content: Crunchy tempura esp the vegetables

this is one of the best western food i've eaten! they serve restaurant style food in a hawker centre, and the food is really worth the money! the food is not very expensive and the portion is really reasonable, i would recommend trying this!

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Many choice of food to select. Love their teriyaki pork belly n chicken. Only that sometimes miss out order and need to ask again. Usually I pay using favepay n get rebate for my nxt visit but this month I came no more favepay.

Buying snacks for customers but system maintenance cant issue receipt. Waited 10mins system stil not up. Ock should consider having manual receipt as backup so as not to lose some business as a result
Seriously overprice and rude service. Avoid at all cost
The person say closing soon at 730 pm but it closes at 8 smlj
Had the katsu Don, katsu curry rice and salmon roll. Decent meal for the price paid.
The food is delicious, affordable, and the service is attentive, suitable for a large or small Thai restaurant.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
Bangkok Street mookata is probably one of the better places to eat mookata, the prices are quite cheap with less than $15 to $20 per person. The place is quite packed, I suggest coming earlier to book a seat as it can take anywhere between 30 mins to 1 hour for a seat depending on group size.

The portion for food is generous and good and for the large eaters, don't worry, you will be full. I have gone several times and it is always filling

Expensive! Even of you decide to pay extra for something good, this is not the place to go. Average food taste with very few bright points.

The Ebi Tempura Don: the tempura was WAY too thick.
Chicken teriyaki Don: there was more skin than actual chicken.
Aburi Salmon Mentai: ridiculously small for the price
Salmon Aburi maki: only thing I ordered that I cannot complain about.

When they open I was so excited to have Japanese food in the neighborhood, but unfortunately this is not what you're looking for.

This place gets 5 stars as it is the only good joint that accepts reservations at NTU...

Pretty decent selection of food and drinks. Service can always be better.

I was welcomed by the friendliest n helpful staff at AMK Hub branch, Beatrice. Being the first timer here, I was totally lost.. Despite the busy dinner hours at 7.30pm, She patiently assisted me n helped me thru the recommendation. I chose the Premium Beef set, and it was mind blowing.. the Wagyu beef literally melt in my mouth.. Best Kimchi.. Best Soup.. Yummilicious is definitely understatement. I was definitely return with my ‚ÄúVillagers‚Äù Lol

Came today at around 5pm as this is still my niece favourite Prata hotspot. Same usual issue of tables and chairs uncleaned, oily spots on table and crumbs on chairs. They have changes in ordering as now drinks have size difference which was not highlighted upon ordering. All drinks came in large sizes and as from the images below, my niece can't even finish the super large ice Milo. Personally felt that cashier should highlight to customer when ordering and not by default assuming we want largest size. Food aspect is simple, ordered Kosong/Egg Prata won't go wrong and that's the main reason for bringing my family back. Damage was $30++ for 5 Kosong, 3 Eggs, 1 Mutabak and 3 large drinks.
Hor  fun  my choice, never miss
Don't let the normal outlook of the stall fool you. The food is really damn good, flavour starts off like not very much but at the end of the dish you will be wonder where all the food went!
Delicious Muslim Malay Food
Tasted nothing like Malaysia Bak kut Teh and claypot rice. Not worth at all.

Wafer was warm and crispy on the outside. Durian was the cheap kind, on the watery side, hardly any sweetness nor was it aromatic. And it was $6.80. Only went to try it because of some food blogger. And I wanted to believe it was good. Disappointing.

Plenty of ingredients and feels cleaner than other indian rojak stalls (didnt see any flies). Loved the potato and beancurd. Dipping sauce is served hot and on the sweeter side. $6 for the whole plate.
Love their Western food. ‚ù§‚ù§
Fried mee goreng look good but on the blant side

Probably my first & last time eating @this restaurant. Had dinner last night, sad to say, the restaurant was unable to cope with the promotions. Observed some customers started to complain on food serve not hot, flow is slow and potion is miserable. Some even left without waiting for the 2nd round of order.üò¢

Below average roast meat, poor service, overprice.
- No menu to see the price. Ordered 1 plate of Êï£Êãº 18$ (roast duck, roast pork, char siew).
- 1st bite, make me wonder why so many people eating compare to row of  stall beside it? Taste cannot make it, oily fatty and not crispy.
- Rude uncle using the dirty cloth to wipe the chair just before we are sitting down.
Zero star for it.
The food was a huge disappointment. I used to come here often a few years ago and nothing tastes the same now. They probably changed their chefs, and skimmed on the material. Service was top-notch.

Don't expect restaurant fare, in fact, Tamako's greatest selling point is the very heart-warming, homely meal you can't help but get addicted to.

Cozy place but still spacious: Portions are quite generous and doesn't really break the bank. 9/10 for me with the missing point easily gained if you request for the sides to be served separately.

Will be back!
Very good staff and experience!!! Good time for team bonding
Decent for a coffeeshop western. Cheap too. Despite long queue and only 1 uncle cooking, food come out fast and hot. üëçüëçüëç
BBQ sticks taste great..

Hi there,

I love your food and there's no doubt on the quality. But recent my 2 delivery orders missed one item each. Last time set menu fries was not packed and today chipotle mayo was not packed. While understanding busy delivery orders, it is important to ensure customers to receive what they have ordered. Would appreciate more attention to pack better next time. Thanks.

This place serves the most innovative prata creations, as well as fantastic well-rounded normal pratas with delicious drinks.

Their pratas are always sweet, eggy and delicious, their curries a mild spicy, sweet, milky and full of flavour, their murtaburger is the bomb, their tandoori chicken murtabaks are always juicy and never dry, their poached egg hollandaise sauce and ham combo is delicious, their portobello mushroom and mozzarella cheese pratas defy all expectations while their briyani is soft, dripping with a melt in your mouth lamb shank.

If you don't have a quirk for crispy pratas, or a preference for spicy curries and just don't know where to go - this place has the quality and variety down pat. Their kopi cinos and the cinos are super yummy too.
I love having my lunch here. the atmosphere is chill and the windows are bright. What a Beautiful day~ Thank you Phillip for giving me this strength. See you again!

The breaded chicken cutlet is big and well fried but the meat is bland. The tenderness of pork ribs ($16.90) is decent, comes with garlic chilli sauce which is moderate sweet.

The corns are sweet. Curl fries are well fried. Fried rice and mashed potato are average. Coleslaw is watery and below average.

In general, the portion is huge and main dishes taste better above average. Quick fix in the neighbourhood area.

It‚Äôs was my birthday treat at this restaurant. The food and the ambiance was fantastic!!! The dishes were different and so sooo delicious. I love the sambal stingray Bakar and mutton Satti sorru .
I must give a shout-out to staff Mathi for his great service and hospitality at seema . Thank you staff (Naren & mathi )of semma for allowing me to celebrate my birthday there at 12 mn giving us abit of time to clear up our food and drinks .
Thank you for your wishes too. The food, service & ambiance made my day.

I gave a 2star only because the sides of the Hokkai Seafood BBQ tasted off/sour.. (like those u will find in example: mixed veg rice the vegetables left for quite awhile it starts to go bad). The Ramen was good though.. Hope the team will conduct regular checks during their off peak..

Hi Sir/Mdm,

My visit was at 07/04/21 17:27 and table 56.

I just want to feedback for you and your team to take note as other customers might not be that understanding or forgiving.

Your food is good, don't let the good name be pulled down by these small areas..

Usually enjoy the century egg porridge, red bean banana and crystal dumplings here (not at our recent visit however). Find the other standard items - siew mai, har kao, char siew bao, liu sha bao, carrot cake - quite average. Not a fan of the egg tart (neither buttery nor flaky) or chee cheong fun (too thick).

We visited a few times in the last 2 years when they stopped push cart service. Now that they have resumed that, satisfaction has dropped somewhat. The fried items were dripping in oil. Given earlier experiences, will give it another shot before revising ratings downwards.
I'm really sorry but have to say quality is quite bad, broth tasteless, meat is hard. Got stomach-ache right after the food, terrible. Not worth the money.

If there is a zero star, I will give that. Young man forgot my ckt orders when there are NO customers around. Collected my money and continue playing game till I check on him 15mins later.
Claypot rice prepare by the fat guy is so so. Not enough meat and lap chiong. Not fragrant compare to hawker centre.

We order shrimp, puffer fish (is sweet, I think kid probably like it alot) and salmon don . Value for money ‚ò∫Ô∏è look at the menu you might think it costly  , but the portion is huge(can share as 2pax), as you can see the unagi don üòÅ

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Fast to get seated due to ample seating spaces even during lunch time today. Only about 10-15 mins to get our food after ordering.

The meal which comes with either an oyster vegetable or 3 dumplings is very good! Always order extra rice because their rice portion is smaller but their rice is so yummy. Sticky and fragrant, addictive!

Although the bill came up to $20 for two because we added extra char siew and gizzard to our chicken rice sets, it‚Äôs totally worth the money for such a satisfying meal. It‚Äôs easy to spend $20 in town on food that‚Äôs way less satisfying or quality.

The ultimate prata series are savoury. This is the to-go place if you are looking for creative creation of prata dishes. Would have given a 5 stars if not for the long wait (mostly due to slow customers turnover for dining in) and the gap in service (table not cleaned thoroughly).

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Order from grab food , no sauce no chili when i order half chicken. Taste dry
Spicy Spicy Spicy üå∂üå∂üå∂üå∂üå∂
This is our first visit. Impressed by the nice food and ambience.

Measly portion for something worth $28. Overhyped and over rated. And give 2 small containers for sauce. The standard cucumber and onion also nowhere to be found.. like only a handful of those.. literally handful. Buyer beware, if you want to waste money, there are other places with more portion that can give cheaper and same quality
Soup is yummy. Meat is well marinated. Prawn is fresh, scallop is big and delicious. Overall is good. Worth the try. Will definitely come back again.

Pretty large portion for the price. Ordered multiple times and quite like the food. Generally prefer their grilled options to their fried options, and some of my favourites are Grilled Dory, Chicken Chop & Fish & Chips. For sides their curly fries, fresh salad and mac & cheese are pretty good imo. Portion for pastas is kinda small, so I wouldn't go for them.

Tried their signature frog pot (original) and thought it was not bad. The soup goes really well with the rice. The grilled eggplants was garlicky and went well with rice as well. Egg plant is def a must try.
The lamb skewers were OK, not gamey at all. The tomato egg drop soup was a little bland but considering the strong flavour profiles of the other dishes, I was OK with it.
The cold cucumber dish was so-so tho. Would recommend ordering their grill veggie skewers instead.

Service was a little slow considering that there wasn't a lot of customers in the shop. The interval between the dishes were quite big and the cold cucumber dish which is an appetiser came right at the end. Def an area worth improving for the shop.
Nice place to eat at. Food nice. Price ok

I bought lontong and mixed rice. I was so happy the lontong is good. So good. The mixed rice which I have beef rendang, cockles and vegetables taste is outstanding. If u are at Toa Payoh in the morning don't miss this shop for breakfast. Worth the money. Outstanding overall experience

Their pasta is way much better than Pastamania.
Price may not be so student friendly.  But at this point of time, there is a overall hike in food price for Singapore.  I am glad they didnt compromise on the quality.
Good place for thai korean foods...

Very decent Japanese BBQ chain!

As it‚Äôs name suggests, they do have a dine-in limit of 50 minutes per table, which actually is more than sufficient, given that the meals here are individually prepared, and are cooked within minutes.

Prices are rather affordable, but could add up really fast once you start ordering the ala carte dishes (100g of chicken at $3.90, super worth it!)

Will definitely return, given the quality and price! üëçüèª

The chef hand makes the fish balls and fish cakes. This is as authentic as it gets. Noodles (dried version) are al dente, topped with aromatic scallions and sauce. Be prepared to queue because everybody loves good food.
Super place.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Friendly customer service and very delicious food..üòç

i have never been to this restaurant or hotel. However, recently, i need to organise a little gathering in this vicinity. Happy Joy came up in the search. So i took a gamble. Ah Heng has been absolutely professional and helpful, not only in the arrangements, but his recommendations for ordering of food. The coffee pork ribs and the fried egg white scallops turned out to be really superb. The cuisine is Cantonese and though the pricing appeared steep initially but the servings is pretty substantial. Am glad to find another awesome restaurant in the vicinity. Thank you, Ah Heng!!

The steak were absolutely delicious, perfect medium steak..
Thanks for the free nuggets for the birthday freebies!
We ordered via food panda, order# x0nh-guj3.
Cheers team.. Next time again üòçüëåüèΩ
I like their pratas because not so oily, and due to the crowd, pratas are fresh and warm.

Our 3rd time here . A really nice drinking chillout izakaya place that we chanced upon .  We popped in for drinks once and were  surprised that the food  here are really good . Has been a weekly meetup place since that . Highly recommended !

3.5 stars. Ordered the chicken curry with prata and yam paste. The curry was delicious, thick and flavourful. The prata can be crispier. The yam paste was at best average, tasted powdery, not the authentic orh nee.

We tried three different carbo - bee hoon, thick noodles and claypot rice. They were all yummy! Fortunately, for us, we ordered in advance; if not, we need to wait at least 30 minutes for the claypot rice.
Be prepared for one hr wait caz the Claypot rice was cooked from scratch! Tried the salted egg bitter, hakka fried pork, and of course Claypot rice. They were amazing

The food is all very delicious. Went there to get a whole fish, which I looked forward to but too bad, they are out of all the whole fish and crabs. So we went ahead to order the rest and its all delicious. Worth the price. The place was very quiet at 7pm, as if I booked the whole place for myself. Service was great. Just too bad I can't get my whole fish. Will definitely come back for more, hopefully there's a whole fish available next.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: ASTONS in Singapore is awesome! I always love the value for money. Their food is delicious, generous. Especially love their pasta salad! Yummy max. It's usually packed with people especially during weekend evenings.
Can‚Äôt go Malaysia now, at least can come here
Value for money. Taste quite good

Amazing experience for my birthday celebration two nights ago! Food was delicious as always, portions were huge too. The lambshank mandhi I ordered was tender and soft. Ondeh2 cake tasted great too. Always loved the Malayan Council hospitality, as experienced at other outlets üëçüèº Thank you to the friendly staff for making sure we enjoyed our dinner there!

Utterly disappointed with this family restaurant. Maybe because family so waiter & waitress who looks like bro & sis are super grumpy and rude. You step into the restaurant and no basic manners to greet customer. Nevermind. Tell them number of pax and get rude reply. Maybe they are not short of biz. Prices are not cheap for a hdb restaurant. Would not recommend.

6.30am.Nasi lemak.mee siam.lontong.mee rebus.mee soto,is ready for breakfast.Their mee rebus is fantastic when add in tempeh and tahu.
Their lunch is also ready by 1030am.
It's cheap and all their dishes are good and fresh as the Pak Chik gets everything at the nearby market.Never come across any Malay stall compatible to this Stall in terms of good quality food.good pricing for all walk of life.

Totally awesome place to go for Prata. Conveniently located at Springleaf TEL, exit 2.
The plain prata is so good. If you like crispy prata, you have to try their cheese prata.
Also tried their Sugar Paper which was so crispy, thin and good. We couldn't get enough and ordered another one.
HIGHLY Recommended.

Lady with bad attitude is no longer there. A few gentlemen with great attitude made my day.

Food is great
Food is tasty and staff very friendly üëçüèª
Great food & friendly service, reasonably price, tried the lamb shank bryani, it's very good, highly recommended

Love the food and drinks that they serve for their customers, especially their mee goreng ayam mamak! Some of the staff here, however, should learn to be more friendly when taking food orders from customers.

Tea was added with lots of water, asked to change but said that it was like that, but ended up being able to serve much darker pu er. Pretty sure they served pu er they even said they added water because they were afraid we couldnt sleep at night üòá
Pai gu was really hard!!
worse on top of all these is that toufu which is the fastest to make was not even served after 2 reminders...as we see food on other tables streaming in.
WORSE DINING EXPERIENCE DID NOT FEEL SINCERE AND REMORSEFUL.
Great local Malay food. We came with our 3 kids, tried the Mee Rebus and the Gado Gado. Left very satisfied. And all for a very affordable price! Will come again.
The fries are great. It has this soft potato flavour. The fried fish is huge! Had to share with my son. All in all good old school western food
Always delicious ‚Äî same excellent taste since 25 years ago when I started patronizing their food court stall at Northpoint. Their Chicken Biryani is my absolute favorite!

Came here to try after watching their FB marketing Champaign.

Chicken chicken chop with mushroom sauce, $7.50.  At first thought it‚Äôs definitely more expensive comparing with other coffeeshop western food. However they made it up with proportional portions and the mushroom sauce is really good.

Prawn Aglio Olio $8.90. Is pretty decent with 4 beautiful prawns that‚Äôs pretty well cooked.
However I feel that it‚Äôs a bit too spicy on the general side.

Overall it‚Äôs good enough for me to come back once in a while. Next time I‚Äôll try their steak.

Is a Saturday evening, having family dinner hence  we finally came.  Tonight we ordered as if we are in Johar Bahru. Ordered 20 over items.

The sashimi is fresh, curry is nice, upon is nice, fried cuttlefish is awesome.

Wow a very well spend dinner together with my family.  A little waiting time and is all worth it.

Staff here are all super friendly.
Happy mom happy kids.

Definitely a good place for good Zhichar specials!  Why specials?  This family-managed business has absolutely what almost every food hunter would like to find and taste.  Good price,  ample parking lots,  good food,  friendliness,  special chef recommendations although most times have to wait.  With good food waiting is fine isn't it.

Revisited after few months and there's good improvement to the quality of food. Ordered Crispy Salmon Mentaiko, Iberico Pork, Salmon Sashimi(limited time 1-1 promo with UOB) and a Tendon. The Tendon fell short of expectation, but that again ‚Ä¶
Surprisingly waitin time for seats is not too long for a family of 5paxs, 15mins, on a Sat, 1315H. Food is tasty, portion is reasonable. Service is okay.

Had high expectations for this place, and ordered their Angus Steak for $35. Steak was greasy and overcooked ‚Äî requested for medium rare, but got almost well done (see picture). Apparently their standards have dropped; went at 12pm when it was not yet crowded.

First time trying with my family of 3. Previously they don't have dim sum but they do now.

We had:

1. Steam carrot cake
2. Steam beancurd roll
3. Steam Xiaolong Bao
4. Steam Prawn Chives Dumpling
5. Seafood Roll

Dim sum no GST but ala carte has.

Total damage is about $35.
Decent but overly priced.

Ordered 2 rib-eye steaks with garlic merlot sauce at $16 each thanks to Shopee. Redemption was fast and easy. Good quality for the price - steak was juicy and tender with minimum amt of fat and loved the garlic merlot sauce, curly fries was crispy (I suspect it's the frozen ones you can get at the supermarket), corn was sweet and well flavoured, but I found the coleslaw to be too sweet. Overall, highly recommend!
Nice food at an affordable price.
Horrible attitude and service despite the decent food. Shop was empty at 11:30 and 3 out of 4 people have arrived but they won't let us order the food in advance.
Tried their off peak hour 1 for 1 deal. And it was ok. Food portion was huge. The doneness of the beef was overcooked when we ordered medium rare. The chicken was marinated well and delicious.

Bought 2 big pork buns yesterday morning from compass point  sengkang.
Upon reaching home,  ate both and realize that the meat inside clump together and completely not tasty.  The buns must have been  kept overnight and heated up again otherwise the meat ought to be loose.
Hence there isn't any quality control or seems to be lacking.

Good value and delicious ala carte buffet with generous portions. Seeing previous reviews, they have stepped up and the food was served to us hot and fast. Star of the menu got to be the soon hock fish, ee fu noodle and the sharks fin. Our table of 5 never stopped eating. Highly recommended.

Superb prata. Slightly crisp on the outside, very fluffy on the inside. Curry is good as well and theres dalcha as well.

A much better place for your prata fix than a certain place two MRT stops down.

My FamBam- 4 non vegetarians and 4 vegans- had lunch on a weekend. Mr Suresh, the owner, oversaw the order of the vegan items(see photo) and brought them to our table. What a personal touch! Some of us ordered the Amra juice which was like a cross between the sugar cane and the Amla fruit(Indian gooseberry). We loved it. They say: The way to a (hu)man's heart  is through his/her stomach. Grace's Pot lives up to it.Thank you Mr Suresh...for the reasonably priced finger licking food and to yours and your staff's personable service despite it being a busy Sunday dining hours:-)

Food wise dont have to say so much. THE BEST . however i would like to compliment one of the staffs over there. her name is Jun Ning. i missed my queue number however she did her best to find seats for us as we have kids. Her positive attitude bring up the whole place over here. Nice food, nice staff, happy customer :))

This is authentic Hakka Restaurant. I'm so happy when found this restaurant which served authentic Hakka dishes.

The restaurant environment here looks like 80s. There is also lantern hanging with lantern riddles. Heard from the owner if guess correctly, may have prize.

Ordered some Hakka dishes like Miced Meat Noodle, Fried Prawns with Hakka Wine, Fried Yam ball and Yong Tau Fu.

I love the Hakka dishes here. Definately will come again....
Very nice ambience with awesome dishes tastifully done.
Food was pretty decent and the queue was pretty long. However, the food would have been better if it‚Äôs cooked longer.

My husband found us a $50 cash voucher for the price of $35 on Chope (valid between 11:30am-12:00pm Mondays-Friday). Timeline was tight but we were in the area so it worked out. *Note: We were informed the voucher would work for everything on the menu except the Peking duck platters.*

We arrived around noon on a Thursday. It was busy but we were able to get a table without making a reservation ahead of time. The food was pretty good. The har gow, siew mai, xiao long bao, bbq pork buns were all really tasty! Some of their dishes were on the saltier end - especially the chicken feet. The custard lava buns were really delicious! It was a lovely blend of pineapple bun exterior with custard filling on the inside.

I was really impressed with their service. Our cups were continuously re-filled before it was even empty! Our plates were changed about 2-3 times to ensure we had a clean plate for whatever dish we were having. So thoughtful!

The only thing that caught me off guard was we had to pay to pack the leftovers. This wasn‚Äôt AYCE so it was strange to me that it would cost $1/item to pack things to-go. This has never happened to me in the history of dining out.

Love the cute environment served by Robot, would like to appreciate Andy for giving us his excellent service, wa came with friends to celebrate my birthday, Andy helped to arrange the complimentary dessert with birthday tag on it sent by Robot. Staff with excellent service.
Very good staff and atmosphere
This restaurant has a amazing Indian (North/South) cuisines and drinks to taste it. I like it. üòÄ

Since the new stall replaced the previous one we seldom eat here.. Too much pepper in the sauce.. unable to taste what we are eating.. standard not as good as the previous stall. Ingredients are also not as fresh..
Had lunch but masala mutton I had was really salty. Price is a bit high compared to other Indian restaurants that do similar menu..service staff was not great as well

All the porridge we tried were delicious & we could feel the difference in each variety.

Ambience may not match an expensive restaurant but the price is kept low which makes good value for your money.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
I‚Äôm not usually a fan of Thai food but this stall converted me. Ordered the green curry chicken, kai lan and clear tom yum soup. Super worth it.

2021 update: felt that the standard wasn‚Äôt consistent as of late. But still a good option considering the price to quality.

My favourite Prata, Murtabak and Mutton Briyani Place üòç

Honestly was super crowded to visit on a PH, but managed to quickly get seats upon arrival as people seem to eat rather quickly here

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Food is good. Especially the prata.
Reasonable cleanliness and staff courteous.
Frequently the food bill amount varies. Regular customers can notice it. Most probably the staff make mistakes while they do mental addition of the amount.
It may be a good idea to put a price listing board on the wall for standard items that customers usually buy. This will reassure the customers.
Great food, friendly staff and good price. Definitely will eat here again! :)
Quite innovative, serving by robots train. Even the entrance to table, ushered by robots too. Menu looks nice but not attractive to foods. Can be improved with more unique dishes.

Trying this for the first time and looking at the long queue so look like very popular. However prata is very ordinary. Got my order wrong. Long waiting time. If it‚Äôs good it‚Äôs worth the wait. But 30 mins doesn‚Äôt justify that. Better off going to the market and order the prata and finish eating still less than 30 mins. Consolation they do serve 2 different curry but what‚Äôs the point when it‚Äôs not nice. Try only if you have 30 mins to waste and a stomach for lousy fried dough.
Have not visited this restaurant after my last visit

Chicken is very smooth and tender, Fried beancurd was special and well-cooked. Ordered the Black pepper fish fillet, pretty nice sauce too! Egg was also very nice. Chilli and sauce all very good, but staff tends to be a little rough and noisy while clearing plates. Other than that it was a really good restaurant tho price might be a little on the high side, but very worth the quality
Great western grill at toa payoh central. The shroom oglio aglio and cheese wedges must try when you are here. Coffeeshop is clean and well maintained too.

Food was okay, but on the pricy side. The service was prompt and the vibes was right for a Chinese restaurant. Was there for a weekday lunch, and it was relatively busy. I‚Äôd suggest the weekend dim sum buffet instead for under $40. It‚Äôs more value for the money you‚Äôre paying.

The Set is good portions for two pax, but prawns were very hard & Sweet corn was difficult to chew, preferred baked potatoes but was not allowed to change. Prefer more green veges instead of big pieces sweet corn that's difficult to chew.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: We went to the restaurant with Jumbo‚Äôs birthday voucher (200-100). The dishes are delicious and the portions are quite generous. I think it‚Äôs a good place for family gatherings.
Aunty there taking order super rude just want to earn money

Nice ambience. Food is average. Ordered breaded fish and chips, and the grilled chicken set. Fish is not fresh, the pineapple that comes with the chicken tasted spoilt. If you are looking at value for money, come during lunch for the set lunch menu. Service was ok.
Best North Indian and South Indian Food , very tasty food and good location Yummy C:

Amazing food! The whole experience from start to finish is great waiter is always so friendly and kind. Very tasty and well prepared and can choose among many menu options. Absolutely amazing place to eat, 10 of 10 for every single aspect of this meal, and this is coming from people who know and love great food! The staff ( Danes )  and greeter were very nice. Our waiter was awesome, the staff also worked as a team in bringing and cleaning up our food. Highly Recommend!!!

I eat here every week, always with a smile on my face.
PadThai and seafood TomYam are delicious. A serious must-try.
Also very Friendly staff.
My favorite Thai in SG!

In December i visited 2 Times.
Ty for cooking vegetarian food for us.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Basil Pork with Rice - absolutely awesome. Super tasty & spicy! i love it!!!
Very good sea food place must try

We were not hungry but wanted to eat something before going home. One of my Mom favourite restaurant. The starters is always welcome crackers which we both loved. The fish head ohta (not sure of the spelling) is nice. Loved the mango salad. Tom yum here is very good - best shared.
good beer promo and delicious food at Yalong Bay. have to order their specialty fire chicken
I find the soup not enough taste. Too much water diluted the taste.

Suberp rojak gravy  can ask for another cup if nt enough cause i like to dunk e goodies in e gravy with spoon...other dishes also available like ur regular mee goreng beef steak mee kuah n lots more ...plz come to discoverüòãüòãüòã

This is without a doubt an authentic Thai food place by Thai folks. Even the simple looking hor fun already tastes better than many zhi char, and the Pad Thai is damn shiok. Fried rice also shiok. Will return to try everything else.

Google should allow zero stars because that's how bad my experience was today. I walked in around 3pm and no one bothered to attend to me. Even though there was only 5 tables occupied while staff was just walking around.

After finally being shown to a table, I asked what was the soup of the day. But the staff did not know and said he will check. Was given a QR code to make my order. But it did not work saying the table was closed. Asked one staff for assistance. Was given an abrupt "wait ah". After awhile, asked another staff, given same response. I was finally then given a new qr code. Still no one told me what the soup of the day was.

15mins have since passed since I walked in. I am frankly very disappointed with how far the service standards of Jack's Place have fallen. I have been going to Jack's Place since Yen Sen Building in Orchard Road. I would have fully understood if it was crowded but it was the middle of the day, there were enough staff around and the restaurant was not even 1/3 full.

After 20mins, my appetite was gone and I left.
Food nice

It has been in Ang Mo Kio  since the 80s. Used to be located in the food centre beside Jubilee square. They have now moved to a coffeeshop recently at BLK 347 after a break. Their chicken cutlets and chops are still the most popular. Old school, affordable with a good portion!
Nice Bak Kut Teh and other Chinese traditional cuisine. I was already several times and the service is also very good.

The service was super terrible. Our first and last time here. We won‚Äôt go back again!

There was literally only 5 tables occupied. So I don‚Äôt know why we had to wait so long to place order.

1) waited 20 mins for ppl to take orders. The lady taking the order is rude and arrogant.

2) the lady at the cashier counter. My goodness.. super blur and slow‚Ä¶ she cannot grasp any infor and we hv to repeat many times to her:

3) the india brothers were efficient and better than e two ladies who were front line.. seriously cmi..

4) After eating main course; we ordered payasam and tea. We Waited another 20 mins. We CAncelled the order; paid and left:

With the current issues of food positioning from Sakunthala‚Äôs making rounds in Tik Tok.. we still wanted to support and so came to Sakunthala‚Äôs.. forget it.. Their service is Soo bad that I won‚Äôt come back at all.

Food above average but has given four stars as I find the pricing reasonable.

Worth a visit for all Heng Hua food lovers.
Yummy food paired with exceptional service
Indoor, comfortable, with a very wide range of speciality dishes for both SAFRA members and non-members.
The egg prata is crispy and soft. Fish curry also delicious and pair with teh tarik, awesome. Staff friendly.

Not sure if this outlet is newly open or what.

Went there with my few Indian employees...

Everything also like not available.
No Poori , No Chapati, No mutton soup.. No murtabak...

There are like 6 staffs in the kitchen cooking...
But seems like.. keep getting orders wrong...

The food... Is plain so so...
My mee goreng is tasteless...
And it is like...
They use chicken with bones...
Means it is like..
Those fried chicken they leave at The counter to sell....
When they cannot sell finish...
They use it to cook the noodles....

So as the same for my employee.. mutton fried rice..
The mutton was the mutton at the counter...
Never sell finish..
And used to fried rice...
Close to 4 dishes we ordered...
Are quite badly cooked...

My next table customer was curse and swearing.....
Finish his plate of noodles in like...2mins
And left....

While the customer behind...Was typing to his friend..
How bad the food was...

Left without finishing the food....
I think it was the boss that came up to us...
And asked why we didn't finished the food...

Saw that their other outlet.. got not bad reviews...
But this outlet..
The food is just really not up to standard.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Tim Sum variety remains but the quality had definitely dropped, but taste is still consider ok for a neighbourhood Tim Sum.

The only thing that need improvement is the cleanliness as tables are always sticky as I could tell that the table cloth is hardly rinsed.
It is said that the chicken clay pot is famous. was delicious.
Just found out this halal restaurant  recently & ordered through grab. It serves salmon & unagi meals !! Hard to find halal food that sell this kind of meals.  üëçüëç  love the sauce too!

Had good experience with PW in the past, albeit generally on the pricier side. Not sure what happened, perhaps the pandemic has called for measures, but $7.70 for this chicken thigh and... I don't know what? Scratched my head a few times trying to recall whether this dish should comprise more or whether the delivery guy ate something from it.

Will have to give them another chance sometime.

2nd May 2022, public holiday, took mom to several places but packed came over here as she never step in before.  She was lucky to get seats after I dropped her 1st.  The table is filled with side dishes, I enter 5 mins after and got a shocked.  The honey chardoew is nice, pigs neck braised, haebeehiam and braise peanuts are awesome.  Order the 3 eggs spinach and a plate of steamed chicken  for 1 pax , 1 pot of chrysanthemums tea and we are done.

Mom loved the food as she seldom dine out of her zone ar her neighbourhood.

Staff were friendly and helpful.  Overall my boss said good choice.
Phew...

The dishes were okay for a family of 3 and the Thai style fish was surprisingly better than expected. The claypot eggplant is a must for those who likes. Aside from the limited seats and long service time, the rest are good. Recommended

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Its not bad.. the curries are deep in flavour and tandoori chicken is tender though meat is a little dry. Naan is soft and absorbs all the curry dip nicely

Ambient was good. Not too noisy. Food came relatively fast enough.
Simple to order through the tablet

Food is good but the price?
Hefty and expensive.For someone who is making business here,getting twice of the price that they are able to get compared to when they are making business in their own country is fair enough but when prices ranging from $5+ onwards just for a meal,it is quite pricey I would say.
bad, no space to sit ‚ó°Ãà

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Decent steaks at affordable prices. I went with the ribeye extra cut which came with 2 sides (quite good value). Comparable with some of the steaks I've eaten in Australia. Plenty of seating available but you just order and pay before getting a seat. Good for groups and credit cards accepted.

The food standard has dropped a lot like a totally different recipe. I doubt if they change owner or the staff is new. If I were to give rating, last time was 9/10 now is 1/10. Taste like they just simply stir the panmee with plain soya sauce. Not worth the price paid.

Staff are rude and have attitude problems. Not customers-oriented.

The colors they utilized in their interior design were fantastic. The colors are black, white, and jade green. This is a fantastic mix. I went on a Friday night when it wasn't too packed. ‚Å£

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Ordered this classic pickle and fish fillets and the portion was huge. Definitely worth the money üí∞!!!

Cheapest good nasi lemak Nasi Lemak (S$1) comes with a slice of fried egg, a side of sambal chilli, and a choice of either selar kuning (deep fried mackerel) or ikan billis (deep fried anchovies). If you want both ikan billis and selar kuning, it‚Äôs an additional S$0.50.
Rice is fragrant and sambal chili is balanced.
If you are a big eater, get two packets for $2.  They are sold out normally at 1pm
Yummy Japanese bento in Westgate. Nicely grilled meat with fragrant soya sauce. Nice and polite crew too. Recommended to give a try
An amazing discovery of good food in a hidden niche. Thoroughly enjoyable lunch at a reasonable price.

Finally get to try the food after seeing so many good reviews. Tried the chicken chop and salmon oglio olio pasta. Indeed, the food taste great and especially the salmon pasta. Great customer service as well. Not crowded during dinner time and perfect for unwinding after a day's work.
fast food but delicious
Pack a takeaway lunch here today, new opening in this local coffeeshop, wait time for less than 5 min, overall for the price the taste is good. The rice is not as sticky as other I had which I like.
Value for money. For the price paid, the quality of beef was good. Just have to wait a while in the q

Went to had dinner at Mouth restaurant before CNY. This is my 3rd visit to the restaurant. We are party of 4.
Near to CNY, the restaurant only offers CNY menu sets that consist of 6-7 dishes .
The set menu was meant for 3-4 pax. Honestly , the dishes is more than enough for 4 adults . If you like Chinese food, overall , the food is not bad, typical traditional Chinese food. Damage close to $100 per pax (included GST and service charge)

Quite a hidden restaurant in the mall. Overall the food was good, especially the curry. Not too spicy and eat with bread or rice. The otak otak is different shape than I expected. Haha. Will visit again
Very good Chinese food.

First visit to Malayan Council for my birthday celebration and on top of the generous portion and quality food, the excellent service from the staff who served us is clearly why we'll visit again. Thank you for the lovely drawing and cake.

I found the information regarding what they actually offer lacking online so I talked to a friendly male staff about it. They mainly do buffet and wedding packages but they also actually offer ala carte menu as well. This review is more for posting their ala carte menu photos for the benefit of everyone. I will go back for the food someday.
getting our Malaysian food fix here at least until we get to visit our neighbors up north again.....and very soon we hope...üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

The chicken wings have gone bad and the meat has turned black. I bought them on March 31st. The attitude of the staff was very bad. When they spoke, they seemed to be fighting. When I came home and saw the chicken wings, I immediately lost my appetite. üëéüëé

Been patronizing this outlet for few years. However, standard has been dropping. Especially with more residents shifting to the nearby flats and condos, the service crews attitude is really bad. No smile. And ever waited more than 1 hour for our dinner to be served. After checking with the crews a few times as kiddos are really hungry, they will tell you off saying that why you come at peak hour? (it was close to 8pm) Our kitchen are short handed with just 1 chef. And today, the rice that they served is mixed with short grain and Thailand rice. To cut cost, maybe. Just felt that it does not deserve to our continuous support anymore.
Situated at level 2 and beside the tanjong pagar food centre, one can find the store tucked to the left of the food centre. The food here is slightly more  pricey than the food centre but it is nice!

2nd review dine in 13 aug.
Special call out to the fish in tomato broth , using bean sheets , served with toufu , tomato, mushrooms and white fungus , it‚Äôs really addictive .

fried shredded yam salad  was crispy and light .

1st review Ordered via food delivery dried laksa, diced mushroom
With toufu, fried banana fritter with red bean and steam bean curd roll.  The dried laksa was very good , flavour and aromatic .

General service is good. 5 stars because of this lady who really made our dining experience  positive. She will check on us to see if chilli is enough, or needed to pack when she saw some leftover. She also make sure that our additional takeaway order is only  when we almost done with our dine in. So that we won't have to wait too long and still warm.

However the food quality has dropped. The chicken meat is hard, still tasty and the skin has some obvious "feather". Rice is still good.
Peggy was very professional and went above and beyond in her service. Hope to see her again on my next visit!

THE PLACE FOR NASI LEMAK WITH THEIR SAMBAL POWER.. NASI SAMBAL GORENG IS ALSO BEST..
Delicious food, affordable price.. Satisfaction guaranteed.. The least packets of nasi lemsk i bought is 6.. So u guys tell me, how can it not be best..

First visit was yesterday, second visit was the day after.

The above is the testimonial to how awestruck I am with the fishball and the taupok with fish paste.

Fishball has a slight chew to it. It's like eating a real tender rare wagyu beef but it's fishball!

The taupok with fishpaste was the highlight for me. Soaked with the savoury soup, a bite of it is simply a piece of heaven for me.

The noodle wasn't in the best shape as it was bought home instead of eating it at the coffeeshop.

Highly recommend it but do expect to wait a while.

Queued for 15-20 min, the queue may seem long but the uncle was real quick so it moved fast!

The dimsum buffet was priced ($26/pax) reasonably for the quality of food and convenient location though lacked variety. Some hits and misses, the prawn wrapped in beancurd skin was probably the best item in menu. Siew Mai was average, a tad dry, shrimp dumpling was also tad dry and the dumpling in red oil wasn‚Äôt good. Chee chong fun, egg tarts and har gao were missing from menu. Saved by the better dessert and cheerful service staff. Overall experience was good.

One of the best indian food I tried in Singapore. Some dish you can't even find in other restaurant. Recommend to order their claypot rice which is damn delicious, I even dabao another for supper. I forgotten the name on the menu thou.

Authentic Shanghai food. The menu is rather limited and a bit hit and miss over all. Some dishes are good, e.g. small wonton, yellow chive fried egg, others are pan fried Pao, scallion oil noodle are just so so.

2 small gripes, cash only and don't have white rice (yep, not typo, it's a Chinese restaurant that does not let you order white rice)
Tasty and affordable. Need to wait for a while during peak period. Staff are all friendly.

Visited again and decided to post another new review with new menu they introduced. Early bird before 12.30pm on weekdays get 25% off. It was a long overdue CNY team lunch and we enjoy the foods and had great chat.

We order a la carte dishes from the menu, didn't manage to take all the food photos. However, here is the listing on top of what had posted, Fish maw soup with seafood and wheatgrass tofu with seafood.

The foods always amaze me with the ingredients used and enriched taste in all of them. The environment is cozy since we got the table near the window and we order the Bailey drinks that were really rich, must try.

One of the better vegetarian food here in SG with very reasonable price.
Must try are the Buttered Abalone Mushroom & Caramelised Yam Dices. Cannot stop once started.

A true hidden gem!  Tucked away discreetly on the second floor of a shop lot on Purvis street, you won‚Äôt notice it unless you go looking.

Hands down, probably the best meal I‚Äôve had in Singapore.  We started with the Hamachi Carpaccio that was topped with generous truffles shaving and ikura, drizzled with truffle shoyu - the yellow tail was so fresh and every bite was simply a flavour bomb hit!  Next came the Tanoke Beef Bowl (rib eye).  It was a masterpiece, where the meat just melts in your mouth, so tender, juicy and cooked just right. The creamy yolk from the onsen egg made it the perfect sauce to go with the Niigata rice.  Soooo yumms.

They also do Sake pairing but not much of a drinker‚Ä¶. But definitely a must if you are a sake lover.

Also love the sleek decor & vibe, making it a great place for date nights or girlie get together.  Staff were all attentive and ready to serve.

Can‚Äôt wait to come back and try more items on the menu.  Highly recommend!!

Really disappointed in their red velvet cake. 3 years ago, we ordered a full 500g red velvet cake and we were served a majestic 3 layered red velvet masterpiece. This time we ordered a whole 500g red velvet again but it was 2 layer of red and 1 layer of cream, and the whole red velvet was covered with coconut shavings, horrible try at a new recipe.

Aside from the unfortunate red velvet incident, service and food quality still remains as great! We enjoyed ourselves.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Since this is rather close to my office, I have been there about 2-3 times.

Service is pretty alright, the service staff is prompt in refilling our tea and would recommend us dishes each time (but they won‚Äôt let us know if we over ordered, so have to really gauge yourself).

Food wise is okay, portion is generous even when it‚Äôs $1 promotional dishes. The fried veggies were quite nice, xiao long pao tasted so-so.
Not open on Sunday. Please update info on Google

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Good service is definitely! Able to tell that apart from thumb up on service, outstanding standard of cleanliness which is rarely can be seen in other restaurants. There is a lot of different varieties of food!
Super economical and delicious. It is just small and abit noisy during lunch time.

Great chicken rice for a reasonable price. I ordered the white whole chicken. Soya sauce complimented the chicken well, and other dishes such as the sambal Kang Kong and crab meat steamed egg. Great atmosphere too. The app only applies for take away. Would recommend this place.
Value for money. Its an affordable unique buffet very neat way of eating using the malaysia style of lok lok. They will help you fried your food as well as steam boat.

Ok to have simple meal. The service is ok. But not happy with the waiter Sam.. we arrived early and made reservation but arranged bad seats while others got better view one without reservation.
The food is ok but the eel is not ok, so suggest to go for the rest if possible.
Do not understand what I say like I say don't want vegetable

Food was not hot, just little warm.
Salty and small serving.
Chilli not fantastic.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: I order a Roti john chicken with cheese black pepper  and then u just give me a egg n onion?????where is the chicken go????

Disgusting food, everything is overcooked and overpriced, how can everything still taste bland with all the garnishes and ingredients.

Upsized/Jumbo set is just double portion of rice. lol!

Visited the AMK hub branch on 5th March, 1:27pm bought the maki mix set that costs $8.20. Despite their sushi looking less appealing compared to other takeout sushi competitors around in the mall like Mr Sushi@ NTUC and Kuriya‚Äôs, I still decided to give them the benefit of doubt and went ahead with my purchase. Upon consuming, I was appalled by the sourness of the chuka maki. I then sniffed and taste tested the rest of the set and realised they have all gone bad too. Sadly, the only ones that were still edible were the mini cucumber, tamogo + crab stick ones. The sushi rice were tad disappointing too, lacking in the vinegary touch that usual sushi should have. Service wise was fine but food quality could have been better.

Came with hubby and kids on Sunday late afternoon . Kids and pets friendly . Quite a busy cafe at that hour so I think quite suitable for noisy kids to dine in . Ambience was great as I faced to a small tropical garden ! Love the plants especially for plant lovers . haha . I think chicken croffle was not bad-recommended . English BF and spam fries soso. Cappucino can be better ( quite bitter ) as I think the other cafe around the corner has better coffee . I was expecting better coffee

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Good place / cheap price

I stay in the area and probes this western is one of the best tasting in my area. Aglio olio and breaded chicken is my favourite, value for money and big portions $7.50. The menu itself is good. Chicken and lamb dishes are well season.

This is our fourth times here.  Their Thai food are nice and delicious. Menu has alot more variety than previous owner.  Price are reasonable and they serve quite fast. Will sure patronise often and highly recommend for all to come. The fried chicken skin is crispy and nice. Tried their red ruby today, if the ice is crushed ice will taste better.
Ramen broth is a little too salty. Waitress told me in future could let them know.

Now newly located to science centre and still out most favorite restaurant in neighborhood. The fish briyani is excellent and different from other restaurants. They have fish manchurian cubes instead of tawa fried vanjiram in briyani. They dont use food coloring which i personally like a lot. We visited on a friday night for dinner and there was queue to be seated. Service was good and fast. The place is bigger than their earlier location (opp. to phoenix LRT). Mutton gosht curry was tasty. Pappad with mint chutney will be served for free.
Had a family meal, the service was great and so was the food. I made a booking and good thing I did it because it was soon busy for lunch!

Went for the lok lok buffet, there were a large variety to choose from. Service was excellent as well! Will definitely visit them again!
Damage: 26.80
For Satay peanut sauce +$6 for the table.

My family has dined at Aroy Thai for over 20 years from when they used to be at Siglap and Funan. I‚Äôve had the food from their East Coast outlet quite recently too but it was our first time at the Novena branch and the quality was even better!

We were there on a weekday for lunch around 1.40pm and thankfully there were quite a few empty tables. Service was really prompt and our first dish arrived less than 3 mins after our order was placed! We had the pad thai, garlic kailan, seafood tomyum soup, grilled pork and stuffed chicken wings. Even though we had asked for the soup to be less spicy, it was still pretty potent so it‚Äôs best to ask them to dial back on the spiciness if you‚Äôre not someone who can handle it well.

The portions were also pretty big and we had some leftovers. Very glad that the quality has stayed great over the years!

Large amount of Indian and Malai food varieties available here,.. I personally like their service, maintanance and their coffee. For food taste i would like to give 5 stars ratings, but in hygienic matter can give 3 stars only. Overall it's recommendable place to have good food in Yishun.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Looking for something different for lunch today and found this great place with ample parking. The dishes are excellent and reasonably priced. There is a 10% service charge and justifiably so as service is prompt and good. Will definitely come back.

Dirty, unhygienic, and eating again with hands that used to touch money. Anti gave me the smell of the eggs, so when I got home and checked it out, the smell came from the eggs.
money is too bad

24hrs. Great teh tarik, teh halia, wide range of drinks choices. Love their Nasi Paprik, Maggi Goreng, Masala & Paper Thosai, pratas, fish curry. I'll be going back to try more items on their menu. Very attentive service. Windy, open dining area.

One of the worst Boon Tong Kee restaurant which is at Ang Mo Kio. The claypot liver was not cook properly looks like dirty liver. The claypot liver cook at Beliestier Road is so much better. The chicken rice is not serve hot, got to shout at them then they attend to you. Never eat there again

I can‚Äôt believe that I have not put up a review of Lotus Vegetarian! We have been enjoying their food since 2020 when I took out from their Ubi kitchen. And of course proceeded to enjoy the lovely and bright ambience at their Novena restaurant when it opened.

Today, I stopped by to pick up some dinner. Decided to try something new, cos always eat the same reliable favourites - dry laksa, all the tim sum esp fupijuan (bean curd sheet roll), chasiewpow, jianpow, shuijing pow.

So we had dry laksa (haha couldn‚Äôt resist), French beans with radish, mapo doufu and cordecep soup. Everything is as delicious at home as when eaten on site. 10% discount for taking out too!

Update 10/7/21
Taking the chance to dine in before 5 people can eat together‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs quiet tonite on sat nite with less than half the tables filled. But I‚Äôm sure business will pick up once HA is lifted, so gotta book or wait for seat.

Had the nasi lemak and mutton curry. Both were delicious. Nasi lemak was tasty without being overbearingly rich. Bleu pea rice was fluffy, chilli was sweet and spicy, fried fish pieces were fragrant, lightly blanched lady fingers were dressed in chicken rice chilli, and fried ‚Äúchicken‚Äù pieces (bean strips) were crispy and tantalizing!  Again The mutton curry was tasty but light. There was a generous amount of potatoes and ‚Äúmutton‚Äù pieces in the soupy but not diluted curry which we drank up!

It's first time to try at this restaurant newly open in Jurong Point.

Firstly, the concept is good that we can order the food in system and food will deliver right to your table. So far most of the food quite tasty, I like the ice cream also. For me, the room of improvement is selection of items can be more.

Hopefully along the way, the menu will getting more items selection in future.
Traditional Indian food.  Even with no air con the place is cozy. Taste is decent and so is the price.
Ordered the mixed grill and chicken cutlet.  Chicken got one kind of smell though.
Great food, remember to go during happy hour for discount :-)
Blue coloured nasi lemak rice! Must try!
It‚Äôs a kind of sweet tasting soup. Chili sauce wasn‚Äôt quite what I expected. A bit too citrusy. Overall not quite the same as Penang hokkein mee in Penang. It‚Äôs an interesting take though.
They gave me the wrong order. Again. I guess Cheese Fries sounds alot like Bolognese Fries.
Well managed restaurant. Price for the food is reasonable.
One of my top 3 Sichuan spicy diced chicken dishes in Singapore. Taste so satisfactory!
Went there to have reunion dinner. The restaurant is located at the HDB block. Decent food, good service. Paid $468++ for a table of 8. Considered slightly expensive.
Food is nice! Reasonable price‚Ä¶ due to too delicious I forget to take pictures
Really tasty and fresh sashimi and sushi. Pork cutlet wasn‚Äôt that nice. I will skip that next time. Sushi tei tends to quite consistent across branches.

It in a coffee shop. Smoking area is causing the air to feel polluted. The food is better then normal zhi char and lots of variety.
They have one of the best deep fried pork belly

Good food, quite affordable but the service can be overwhelmed when there is a crowd. So you must constantly chase abit.

Overall ok, would go back and try their ox tail.

Delivers by grab and accepts grab pay
Great Food... nvn fail me whenever I wanted Malay food... love their mee Soto and Chicken lemak and the sambal.

Impeccable service - staff were very friendly and polite. They were also extremely attentive and kept refilling the tea.

Cold crab was good, other food was pretty mediocre. Chicken was extremely salty.

5 stars for the service, 3.5 stars for the food.
Murtabakburger is nice!

Favorite fusion restaurant in the hood. Oysters could have been fresher but for the rest of the dishes - from steaks to fish&chips, no complaints. Come here every year for Christmas Eve / NYE dinner and they never disappoint. If you visit during the non-festive periods, they have senior citizen discounts too!
Nice food, reasonable price
Excellent service. Glad finally able to take condiments. Enjoyed the discounts for tea time meal.

Friendly owners from Thailand.
Authentic and affordable Thai food. Always my 1st choice.

Circuit breaker period
- hours as usual
- call to pre-order to reduce waiting time
- self collection only. (Updated on 16 April 2020)

I move around in Singapore a lot and had a chance to try out this restaurant due to a friend's suggestion. They mentioned they serve Nepalese cuisine and it's rare to find such a cuisine that's located in an old heartland estate like Toa Payoh. The restaurant is spacious and the service staff is friendly. Most importantly, they really do have Nepalese cuisine as stated, alongside a variety of Western fare, which many old folks who dine there go for. (Maybe because they have a senior citizen discount special which was really nice!). We had 2 appetizers and a main course and the serving size for the appetizers were family size but we stillanaged to finish it. It's my first time trying Nepalese cuisine and it's actually quite interesting - worth a try really! I would love to try out the Western fare next if I can! And they currently have 20% discount on ala-carte.
Super friendly staff. Good food.

Located some distance away from the mrt. The omelette, fried rice and red wine chicken are good. The cold trotters wasn't to my liking as there was just much more skin than meat. Overall taste is reasonably good but nothing especially outstanding.

Price wise seems quite standard.

A no frills tze char stall with decent food quality, seated quickly on a sunday afternoon.. especially loved the san lou bee hoon which looked deceptively nondescript but was super tasty. Also really loved the garlic chicken although the signature claypot chicken rice was a little mushy and lackluster. Hakka Crispy pork was a passable dish albeit a bit too fatty for my liking.
Food and service exceeded my expectations. Really like their Red Wine Chicken Meesua!
Good, tasty food. Price is reasonable.

Dined here for the first time with a group of friends. The ambience and food were great but the service was even better. We were well looked after by the crew; very friendly and attentive.

Likely not a typical occurrence but they were very generous on the evening we visited. They kept serving us food we did not order and then explained to us they were on the house üòÇ

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Loved the outdoor atmosphere! Very friendly husband wife owners. Taught us how to cook Mukata well. Thank you very much. Will definitely come back.

Brand New Concept and Ambience..
Excellent hospitality and energy from the crew!

I had their commando satti soru and mutton murtabak. It was sooo good!

The satti soru was perfectly done with the shiok level of spiciness, crunchy ikan bilis and curry leaves.

Mutton Murtabak was perfect. Generous filling of Moist and tender meat. And the accompanying gravy was also full of flavour and thickness for a dip. Aesthetically pleasing presentation!

Ambience was pure comfort. Loved the fusion of nature with their furnishings.
Warm lighting to complement the wood. It takes you away from the bustling street and activity just right outside.

Definitely going to be a regular! See yall there!
2pm on a weekday, short queue. Power mee rebus, with splash of gado gado sauce on top of the chicken drumstick. Last ate this 30 years ago. Happy to be reunited with this iconic dish!

Truly a gem hidden in the heartlands. Special shout out to the Rib-eye steak as well as the Home cured bacon thicks. The ribeye was cooked perfectly to medium-rare and had a very nicely charred crust. The bacon was full of flavor and the juices oozes out into your mouth.

Definitely worth the visit! Prices were decent for its quality as well.
very good mala xiang guo.  luv the scrambled eggs n fried potato. the Thai milk tea is delicious too. a must try for mala lovers
Portion is small... $14 for 3 pcs pork ribs. Not sure if this price reasonable but the taste is not bad.
Was here early so no q. Meat was decent for the price paid. But the hygiene standard definitely needs to be improved. Found a super long strand of hair right in middle of my bowl of rice. Disgusting

An experience taste since day one, never fail to fulfill our needs. Teh tarik the best drink in the house. The crispy prata never ever dissappoint us, the quality of the food variety are wonderful. Fully recommended to all prata lover!

Happy tummy comes happy family.
Terrible wait time. Waited more than 1 hour for my food when they told me it will take 20-30 mins. Some more food so so

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Second time visiting. Great variety of items on the menu, amazing food, fast service (food came within 15 min of ordering), reasonable price. Will definitely return!

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Authentic Thai food at affordable prices
Authentic Thai food with generous portion. Ambience is nice and staffs are attentive. The price is on the more expensive side than other Thai restaurants, but the authentic taste is worth it.

Would rate zero stars if I could. Went there with family and there was this one particular staff who was incredibly rude and by yelling "Wait" when we raised our hand for her attention. When we ordered our food, she messed our order up 2 times. We completely understand if an establishment is understaffed. But rudeness cannot be tolerated regardless. We were very specific about our orders and even repeated it twice. Both times. They still gave us the wrong order and even walked away without even apologising. Absolutely, ridiculous and unacceptable! Will not recommend!

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
Toa Payoh residents are blessed with this well known authentic Thai food stall  situated in the Lorong 7 hawker center.

Im a regular of this Hom Aroy brand in Sin Ming but it was unfortunately closed for a few months since early January. This is the next closest Home Aroy you can find in the central area.

This stall is extremely busy during meal times especially in the evening. Be sure to visit early or be prepared to wait for a bit.

You won't go wrong with the standard dishes like Thai Pork Basil Rice, Fried Omelette Rice and Tom Yum Soup. Enjoy!
Thick robust and flavourful sauce. A bit too sweet, add more chilli to balance it out.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: One of the best Indian restaurants I enjoy visiting. The masala tea is a must-try, best one I've tried in SG :) I've not tasted anything disappointing there so far. Love the naan, love the rice, love all their gravies and their chapatti. They expanded since I last visited and feature a cosy ambience with solid wooden tables and cushion chairs too. Mmmmm! üòç

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Outlet manager Amanda Chin is very friendly n polite. Was surprised she can recognise me and my preference seating area on my second visit. Other serving staff n food taste are also great..kudos to great customer experience !üòÄ

Value for money set western food, kids friendly with kids menu. Place is wheelchair accessible. Also available are premium steaks, lobsters, escargo and wine. For healthy choice, salads are available. Soft music plays in the background, no live band.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Good
Service by Miss Tai is super friendly and welcoming. Food is excellent, even better than some famous Thai restaurant here and Bangkok. Must try the Prawn Vermicelli, Pork Platter and Fried Fish.

Like the atmosphere and ambiance as its inside of temhr bowling centre.
Service crews were quite nice and polite.
Food wise, not bad. Beverage on quite high side.

Located on the second floor and it was a tad confusing how to get up using the service lifts. I ordered via Grab and did a self-collection.

Food was delicious and the flavours were balanced. I like the flexibility of the menu. However, like most salad bowls places around the Tai Seng industrial area, I don‚Äôt find this particularly value for money if I were to compare it to similar places in the CBD, where I pay similar or lower prices for way more protein. So yes, while the food was good, I‚Äôm not sure I might order it again. Especially since macros and nutritional information isn‚Äôt listed like the usual CBD haunts I go to, which are way more transparent.

That said, they don‚Äôt market themselves as a healthy choice, so something to note for people trying to eat better.

I wonder have this store changed new boss??
Their services are not as good as the previous I'd visited, just one customer next to me asking for some more üå∂ chilli, and he only just given a piece, and the customer immediately get shocked "what is this!". Later my turn, I softy asked for more cutter onions, he just pointed on my plate and said that's the onions ( a fewest pieces). Not Goodüò§üò•

Good environment for company event.
They provided big LCD screens for the event and provided tech support throughout the event.
The services provided are above the expectations.
However, the food quality is inconsistent and can be further improved upon.

i love the sambal crispy chicken but today very disappointed
the chicken they give me is totally unacceptable
Why because the chicken drum is skinny with less meat and the chicken bones look more black then the previous
i hope the stall owner kindly look into it as it will affect your business if give this kind of crispy chicken to your customer
Very Disappointed
The Nasi Padang is overprice and the food is not fantastic. It is going to be my first and last time patronising the stall.

Food is precooked and then fry again for the prawn paste chicken wings
Seafood mee sua is actually hong kong yellow noodle
Gu lor york is hard

Overall the food are overated but the price is affordable for all the dishes we ordered
Waiting time is long after they serve the precook xia jiang chicken wings.
Uncle roger will love the MSG as after eating feel so thirsty

We picked TMC @ Winstedt for our staff retreat lunch and had a wonderful time thanks to the team of Ady, Zin and special mention to Shazz and Alexis! The food and ambiance were good and some of us even ordered extra food to take home. We had to make some last minute changes to our seating arrangements and Alexis was very accommodating. She always had a friendly and welcoming smile and attitude and was full of energy throughout. Well done, Alexis and team! üòÑüòÑüòÑ

Pretty shocked to see the rest of reviews right before I started digging in. I got the Chicken Tikka Pasta. On first sight looks pretty good, but the taste really isn't all that. Pretty oily inside as well. Agree with the reviews that the portion and quality doesn't justify the price ($9.42 with GST) Who even charges GST in the school though actually. Don't think I'll come again unless they shape up.

Edit: Original review was a week ago. Please take note of the 5 star reviews here, very fishy. Might be fake ones. How the hell is it value for money when someone else paid 8 dollars for 6 meatballs?

The aunty was SUPER rude, took wrong order and blame it on customer. I ordered pork chop and she gave me chicken chop INSTEAD! Told her it‚Äôs the wrong order and she start accusing that I placed the order wrongly. Is ok, I placed a second order for my pork chop! Frustrated!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Love to be here to enjoy a meal with family and friends! Place is kinda hot and price is reasonable!

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Went a few times. Didnt like the feeling of being ignored. Store wasn't that busy but lady basically just left me standing there while slowly counting money etc. Only managed yo try once tom yum soup average.not coming back.

Nice Asam Laksa and Curry Mee üòã.
To his store manage to satisfy our craving for Malaysia food

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: I ordered the mutton briyani, aloo Gobi and prawn masala. The food was great and the drinks are reasonable. I will definitely come here again.
One of the best zi char stall around in Singapore and most importantly the price is very reasonable, was surprised of the total bill after ordering so much. Will definitely visit again.üëçüëçüëç

Glad that they reopened. The serving size is still as huge as I recall. The chicken cutlet is tender and the amount of bread crumbs used was just right. It gave the cutlet just the right amount of crunch that wasn't too hard like some other places. Would be coming back again. Currently they only have the spaghetti option. Hope they bring back the fried rice soon.

Fish ... is thick.
The ikura ...üò±

Feel satisfied.

After a few places tried,  I guess this will be where I go when I need my sashimi fix in jurong

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Overall Great üëç. Gong bao Ji ding was on the sweeter side. Lesser sugar
Would have been better. Rice was very good, so was barley drink
food is decent, but the service is super horrible. despite a standard western food taste, will never return again. the ill service really affected the experience negatively. will not recommend.

Really love the staff services from this outlet.
Excellent services üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª appreciate

Will definitely do another review for the food :)

Will be back.

Has both indoor and outdoor seating. Reservations recommended if you want indoor seating.
Pork ribs were tender and well marinated. Sweet potato fries not bad; has a abit of a crisp.
Arrabbiata Linguine is pretty spicy (fair warning)

The cutleries are beautifully decorated, food is presented pretty before you mix the food together, the wooden furniture and decor gives a nice feeling.

Service was prompt and I noted they have chairs available for children.

Food is mediocre to my personal taste. The overall taste is light. While the noodle is springy and nice, the broth and the rest of the ingredients doesn‚Äôt seem to come together well. And the dish has abundant of soup compared to the contents (the vegetables floated while the rest of the ingredients drowned underneath) so a bit of stirring and searching may be needed to find the part you want to bite. The vegetables also look more like garnishes except for the bean sprouts (eg. Coriander, chives, spring onion, flower petals).

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Love the individual sachet. Very convenient and easy to warm up.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: It was a horrendous first dining experience at this notably renowned venue for Teochew cuisine. Regrettably I should have known from the deteriorating quality mentioned in earlier Google reviews. From the start, we had made a reservation via phone call for 9 persons, but we were shown to a table for 8 persons (7+1) When we questioned about that, the lady serving us had no answer and basically just replied that it‚Äôs okay they would add one more seat to a smaller looking table.  It was strange but I thought nothing of it until almost towards the end of the meal when we were again asked whether they could serve mixed fruits platter. That was when it hit me that they had mixed us up with another bunch of guests. Despite repeated complaints, none of the staff looked sincerely apologetic and merely was in a rush to turn over the table for the second round of diners. Apart from that, the quality of food served tonight was not outstanding, and service was rushed and nobody bothered changing plates or pouring tea till we asked for it. The pomfret appeared to be not cooked well, there was redness and toughness in some part of the meat. It is definitely not a place worth the premium paid for food, service, decoration or anything at all. Atmosphere wise, the place was noisy and warm with spot lights all over and little aircon. It was supposed to be a nice welcoming dinner for our guests but tonight it was nothing short of a disaster with the premium paid for dinner; total damage (bill) being more than 500 dollars. Consider seriously, if you really want to come to dine (unless you really have the cash to spare or prefer to take photos of the food presentation). Note: there was no service recovery done at all.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: An alright taste of Thai food available in this small food center. The tom yum kung clear soup bowl is good for a try. Costs 5 SGD, a bit more than other nearby stalls.
I ordered 4 meals through grabfood for breakfast. 1 meal wasn't delivered. maybe the shop missed an order due to high order volume.
Restaurant just at the entrance of the swimming pool. Lots of variety to choose from. Especially if hungry after swimming or using the gym above.
Consistent standard for fried chicken.. try the buffalo wings
Always same good food will be perfect

overall the good quality is good, just that the portion is rather small. didn't expect the noodle quality is so little, tho the taste of the pork noodle is rather yummy. ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖÔºå Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖÔºå ÂçóÁìúÈ•º& spring rolls are all very good. can skip the ÈÖíÈÖøÔºåthe taste is rather mild. the chrysanthemum tea is chargeable, $2.40 per jug, not FOC as commented by other reviews.

Excellent teh halia (tea with a "kick" - ginger water). The roti john (no human flesh here, just a nice toasted baguette with scrambled egg, roasted chicken chunks, tomato-barbeque sauce and mayonnaise!) was fantastic, the nasi goreng ikan bilis (fried rice with crunchy fried little fish) was fresh and hot! Will try other dishes next time...
Friendly Chef , can customize spiciness. Tasty n economical Sichuan food

It's my second visit and this visit was 100% opposite to my last experience in 2021.I was not lucky this round. Even though I specially mentioned to have the soup less salty,
Every dish we ordered was way too salty ! ÈÖ∏ËèúÈ±ºÔºåËæ£Â≠êÈ∏°ÔºåËÇâ‰∏≤„ÄÇ„ÄÇIt was a treat for my 70 year old mom... but because it was way too salty, we didn't enjoy the meal at all. I had to scrape off the excess sauces on the bbq, asked for the soup to be diluted (which is still very salty).
I have feedback to the kitchen when I made payment, not sure if they take this seriously.. But I think I'm not confident of returning anymore. It was a bad experience for my mom who likes Â∑ùËèú. $60 for very salty food that you can't stomach,  not worth.
The location is quite secluded. However, the price would make up for it. Comfort food for those who miss the hometown.

This is one of Collin's' more consistent outlets, taste-wise. For the price, I'd head to El Carbon a few blocks away though, coz the sauces and dressing are more or less the same and service is just a-ok.

My third trip to this restaurant, tried ordering the al carte menu. We ordered their famous Swatow Chicken which is really good, the flesh is tender and skin is smooth and melt in your mouth. The steam minced pork with salted fish is another dish not to be missed. Well flavored with slight hint of salted fish taste. The most surprising dish is the Teochew Kai Lan Fried Kuay Teow with Preserved Radish. Loved the char flavor and rice noodle is not overly oily.
