The preserved radish just add another dimension to the dish. Loved it and looking to come back and have it second time.

Sawtow seafood, been here twice with my parents to have Tim Sum. It is great that they have lift for elderly so don't have to walk up the stairs. Spacious dinning area, Tim Sum spread is fine with plenty of selection, however I prefer that they have a menu for customer to choice and they bring to our table instead having to wait for the server to push the cart and pick whatever you like. It also took me more than 10 minutes to settle my bills. Wish they have better work processes to make it more efficient for customer as well their employees. Very old school Chinese restaurant.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: The tansuyuk and jajangmyeon here is good no doubt, just feels a little bit pricey. For a little better value, get one of their sets! E.g. set A includes dumplings, tangsuyuk, 2x mains like jajangmyeon or jjampong for $53 (before service charge and GST)
Like it's Penang Prawn mee, the taste is nice, but the amount of mee is less/not enough.. The prawn is consider big size..
Claypot not bad, but not alot of meat
Recommended by a friend! Their pan fried bun is tasty and extremely juicy. Must try!

I would say this is the best hot pot in Singapore for me. I tried the famous Hxx , althought their service is impeccable,  the food n soup base lose out to paradise's hotpot.
The soup base here is superb n the ingredients are so fresh. What's more with the discounts of 30% from opening to 2.30pm, 40% from 2.30pm to 4pm, they are much cheaper than Hxx too.

Love and recommend their

1. Authentic Pork Bone Soup Base
2. Bean curd ring
3. Because of the thick n delicious soup,
all other ingredients n vegetables cooked in it would taste awesome esp with the wide variety of side condiments and sauce at $2.2 per pax chargeable.  I would mix coriander,  spring onions, garlic, cut fresh chilli,  pinch of salt, sesame oil n some premium light soya sauce for the ultimate kick.

Complimentary sweet dessert after meal too ü•∞
Delicious mee soto. Worth the queue. Affordable price.

Very rude matured lady staff who told my pregnant wife who was carrying my 1 year old son to leave the restaurant and wait outside in the hot weather to collect the food. The thing is the restaurant only had 1 table filled and no else was standing in queue or waiting for food. Heartless lady. Food has also dropped standards as compared to little india or tanjong pagar outlet. They missed 2 items in my 6 items order and i dont live nearby to come back. No proper area to check the order also.

Didn‚Äôt expect a meal so lovely before we went. The head chef apprenticed in Japan and the dishes are elegant, beautiful and yummy‚Ä¶ the restaurant is a fabulous combination of traditional style and modern style‚Ä¶ we had a very pleasant time there.

The Penang-style charkoayteow is recommended here. Altho fried five plates each time, the koayteow has sufficient 'heat', 2 prawns and egg for a tasty treat. Only missing the cockles and Chinese sausage for an authentic Penang rendition. However, the place lacks sufficient seats so may have to stand around while a diner finishes.

Nice cosy place for a peaceful weekday lunch. My first time here, further down from the famous prata shop. A very low key shop front. I nearly missed it. I went on a Wednesday afternoon. Parked at the public carpark nearby.  The place is cosy and comfortable. Nothing fancy, very homely ambience. Ordered the Wednesday special bento set. Portion is big. Comes with a big pot of tea. The sashimi is very fresh. I love the miso soup. Rice is sushi rice. Overall, I like this place , good food, reasonable price. Will bring my family for dinner some day

The typical Indian food store with lot of variety.
I have to say their indian food taste real good.

The food is not bad, pretty tasty but it is still not even 90% close to Penang food. But points must be given for the effort for making it rather close to the actual food. It can be pretty crowded during meal time so go early. The Assam laksa is good but the char kway teow taste pretty normal. Go go and try if you miss penang food, you won't be disappointed.

Bought 2 Prata here,  Milky Prata (condensed milk) which costed ~$4 and Unami-50 (chicken floss + luncheon meat + cheese) which costed ~ $10 to take away. It has a rather small eating area.

The Prata was considered nice but too pricey and not really worth it. Although most prata shop in the area will have lesser creative varieties compared to them. Tried the mee goreng the second time as well and found it pricey too.

The price on grab is higher than in store so it is better to take away if it is walkable distance.
Such great food for someone who isnt a facility member of NTU. Dropped by for lunch and it was cheap and legit indian food.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Food taste is not good at all, and they served spoiled  dahi vada and fried rice
Food is good and reasonably priced. Try their crab meat fried rice and clear seafood tomyum soup...it is good!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Good place to eat mookata. Very airy and ample wind that makes you not feel hot. Come early as it gets pack very fast. Price is decent too.
Good food, great service and nice ambience. Small but cosy place.

Poor service, QR code to order food was not working, asked the staff she said she will order for me but she never gave me my order chit so I thought maybe she did order but they will give the order chit later. Waited for 15 mins nth came so I asked another staff(in red shirt) and it was only then did she order for me. So I waited for nothing and attitude was 0 stars, it was like I owed her money or something üôÑ it‚Äôs not that I expect top notch service or anything but at least treat people with respect

No matter what you eat, this is the best local food store. Chicken clay pot is the best in Totoro because chicken and cabbage are stewed tightly.

Shrimp chili sauce is moderately sweet and spicy with excellent taste. And the shrimp are quite firm.

Spring rolls are the best with the best combination of shrimp and ham and ginger. It tastes like takoyaki. Is it Akashiyaki because it contains soup? ? Please visit once by all means.
tasty and reasonably priced thai food, worth trying if youre nearby

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Well ventilated food centre and toilets are finally free (used to have surcharge for use).

Claypot chicken rice taste is average, very few pcs of chicken for the amount of rice. Bak kut teh pork is tough and only 3 small pcs with 3 thin slices of fatty pork. Soup has an unpleasant, overpowering medicinal taste of some particular herb. Chendol portion is small with few red beans but quite good coconut taste though somewhat lacking gula melaka. Overall don't bother unless you want to feel angry.

The food here is super authentic. It reminds me of the trips to thailand in the past. I tried the otah (the one in the coconut). I felt that it was really special. The otah had more "coconut" taste in it and it was more flavourful than the other otahs i had. The rest of the food are okay. The quality is there. Prices on the high side. The staff were very attentive as well. Remember to reserve your seats or be prepared to wait!

Heard this is the best fish ball noodles in Singapore, so decided to try it out. No doubt the fish balls and fish cakes are nice with their dry noodles filled with pork lard and shallot oil. Small portion of noodles with fish ball, fish cake and tofu are filling. I personally like their porcelain bowl and soup spoon, made the food tastier (my personal view). We arrived at 10.15am (Saturday 4 Sep 2021) and started queuing, around 5 people in front of us. It wasn‚Äôt too bad, it took 25 mins to get our food. We ordered additional fish cakes and fish balls. Total bill is $18.80 for 2 of us. Worth waiting and definitely will come back. If you come by MRT, alight at MayFlower, take exit 1-3 and look for Block 158. Walking distance from MRT to this stall.

Great stall in a coffee shop to get your pocket-friendly ramen fix without going to the crowded malls. For its pricing, the ramen bowls sure have something going on, especially the soup base. Would visit again! üëç

Good food, feeling satisfied after meal. Worth 15-20 mins wait during peak for the price (I would give a miss if longer). Sufficient staff and fast service. Variety of cashless payments available, use promo codes for some small discounts compared to cash (dependent on the app). Only bad thing is the steamed fish was not descaled properly, have to spit the skin. Parking at night is not convenient in the evening as nearby all red lots. (Reserved for season holders)

Food was so so only. Not sure why so many rave reviews. Very limited selection, no fresh meat, and quantity is small so you dont get much for $1. Broccoli was soooooo thin. Too much pepper. But overall average for lok lok

I visited a decade ago but now although the place is cleaner, brighter and layout neater it is still the taste that finally matters most. On this count and for the Tang Yuan that it is famous for, it passes. Ticked all the right boxes! The fried dumpling is a close second.
Claypot chicken rice had a decent char and overall, quite fragrant with bits of salted fish mixed in. Wait time was a bit long tho. Quite affordable.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: No frills. Not fantastic. Self service. Quite speedy although Coffeeshop was packed full during meal times. Not going to be winning any foodie awards. A rather wide variety available. Very decent dim sum for the price.
Not bad. Will go again.
The prata is nice and cheap and good that it opens till late at night to satisfy my stomach at night. The staff Steven is also very nice to help me with my order.
Still loved their roasted duck w angelica herb.

Peggy at AMK outlet is a very friendly and cheerful staff as she make our food easy to order and a wonderful place to dine in at. A valuable staff an asset to the management considering her age as she no signs of ageing and in very good health. Kudos to her for giving us for such a warm reception!!! üëèüëèüëèüòÄ
Super tasty, highly recommend Chicken Tikka Masala, and Garlic Naan

Not sure why the divided reviews, but the noodles (at least my bowl of) tasted no different to the ones at urban malls. The chicken broth with hint of saba essence is fresh but no lack of punch, I especially like the addition of seaweeds that bring complexity to the soup. After 2/3 to finishing line, ask for a plate of fried garlic slices to bring the taste to next level!

This restaurant has a large menu from Japan's Tohoku region. We ordered a couple of set dinners and a grilled squid. They come with a food warmer beneath. It's best to let the warm warm up. The steak was well marinated and soft. The squid was not to my liking. It was okay but slightly fishy. All in all a decent dinner on the average side.
Roti prata at its best for service! Curry is thick (if you like thick curry) and mass production of prata!
The best indian muslim food ever been coming here seen 2008....

Had their 3-Kind Buta Combo Jyu. It was rice (don) with grilled chestnut pork belly, pork loik, and Iberico pork jowl. All of them tasted great with the help of the chilli powder. The waiting time was okay. A bit expensive, but would say it‚Äôs worth it.

Ordered (as pickup) from food panda many times

Today (29 april 2022)
i ordered truffle fries and the fries were re-fried so many times, the inside is hard. Never ordering again.
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
2nd time in here, first time was when they‚Äôve just opened(bought a dry cake), so giving them a chance since a lot of reviews say food is nice. Coffee wasn‚Äôt bitter, just had a slight tinge of sourness (I don‚Äôt add sugar to my flat white), food tasted good. Lunch for 2 mains with one soup and drink was $30 (rounded up)

The BOGO (buy one get one) free deal which is applicable to take- away is definitely worth it!  The wagyu may not be the best as they don't entertain the doneness of the meat (meat is well done) and the foie gras is probably from duck (and not goose) , it is huge, but the price is certainly right! The sashimi is definitely top grade and really fresh! The kurobuta pork is delicious and there is 1 abalone in it !

5/12/2021 - returned for their Omakase Teishoku. Teishoku means the meal is served all at one go. It was good and included sake which we could take home instead of drinking there, but they gave us only 1 bottle although there were 3 of us.
Salmon sushi had a weird rotten fish smell, would not recommend for raw sushi

Great food at great pricing! Recommend the Ê∞¥ÁÖÆÁâõËÇâ!
I would drive all the way from Jurong to go eat there again!

Come here for prata on the crispier side - I had the kosong and the cheese + egg and both were great. Cost is on the pricier side, and the curry serving isn‚Äôt as generous as I‚Äôd hope. Quick service though.

Ordered Pork Chop fried rice with fish roe. Fried rice is good. Its taste like zichar style and seems similar to King of Fried Rice. Wasn't expecting the server to hand me a tissue but it's a really nice service.
Prata was ok but could have been crispier. A lot of other foods to choose from.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Bad food, fries were reheated without the normal seasoning, ordered the fried chicken and the flour covering the chicken was burnt. Oil was dripping from the chicken. Wouldn't recommend.
Reasonable price for a Sichuan dinner. Enjoyed very much for the quality of cooking is even better than those at town. Must try !

The restaurant provide great variety and the taste was ok. It was a short queue for weekend lunch. Green tea is refillable. The kids utensil and cup are not properly clean, I doubt if they disinfect the utensils.

All time fav for their pasta! (Aglio olio), cheap and affordable!

They also allowed to upsize your pasta portion which is great!

Reading some of the reviews here are quite entertaining, as though like the prices were hidden and you got a culture shock when the price came up ü§£ #facepalm
My favourite nasi lemak in Yishun. Cheap, good and delicious! Beats the one in Chong pang hands down. Took one star away because consistency can vary.

One of the more famous chicken rice restaurant in Singapore. Ordered their signature steamed chicken and also the fried chicken. Chicken wise is good but not the best. However, the fried chicken can be a bit dry. Also ordered the sweet sour pork, fried mixed vegetables, barbecued pork and the soupy spinach with Yong Taohu. The other dishes are great and complements the soft fluffy flavorful rice very well. Highly recommend their sides especially the barbecue pork. Ambience is good and service is prompt and efficient. However, can be crowded during lunchtime. Overall a good dining experience for family and large groups.
Nice resturant with nice fresh sea food
The best Milo I‚Äôve ever tried. Food here is amazing
Jenny is a very pleasant lady who never fails to serve with a smile. Great personality.
Aglio olio chicken cutlet üëç
Service crew has always went above and beyond to ensure a good dining experience.Food quality is good. Highly recommended!

First time here. We had the tomato & the original. It was ok. Tomato broth was pleasantly fragrantly, but the taste was on the stronger side. If you prefer something lighter, the Original is better. For me, nothing in particular yearns me to return. Gyoza was a tad too oily for my liking.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: The food is quite good. Better than canto paradise.

First time try the coffee at the new drink stall ÊÄ°‰øùÁôΩÂíñÂï°. I came ard 3 pm. The ice coffee is come with coffee jelly but coffee jelly is out of stock and there's no choice of coffee without coffee jelly. It will be better if there's the choice of ice coffee without coffee jelly.

Claypot rice increase in price but meat portion reduced. Taste not as strong n sauce lacking. Oysters r alright but the ckt lacks wok hei. Guess the chef r still young n attitude needs improvement. Will visit kopitiam w better enviromment n selection of food. Price pt higher but better food the least.

Price wise is alright.
Freshness is good.
Food wise taste normal.
Portion is just nice.

Regular Bowl($4.50) - 1 Main, 2 sides.
Olive Rice(Main) - Felt the one the one you eat with porridge, those bottled pre-made olive.
Sweet Corn(Side 1) - Normal corn lor.
Mock Fish(Side 2)üòã - This is nice. Crispy, fragrance, tasty.
Japanese sesame sauce for drizzle

Creamy Scrambled Eggs(Add-on)- Savoury, creamy with a pinch of pepper sprinkle for the perfect gooeyness in your mouth.
Prompt service, servers are pretty attentive when we request to refill drinks. Food are good as usual.
Cheap and good taste.

This place was recommended by my friend because of their Sea Bass (fish) promotion at $12.90. Good price for its taste and I was really satisfied. Initially wanted to order the steamed kind but unfortunately, it‚Äôs already out of stock. Guess it‚Äôs already good. Will definitely come back for the steamed style. Of course, Thai meal won‚Äôt be complete without Tom Yum soup. I opted for their Tom Yum seafood soup and it was a bomb! Can‚Äôt wait to come back soon.

Their Bento sets are really nice and premium. The only problem I have is only 1 Vegetables choice which is Kai Lan and nobody‚Äôs favorite. The restaurant at AMK is getting dated and is in dire need of a renovation.
Scrumptious thai food! The pork belly is a must have!! üî•üî•üî• staff was friendly and even recommended us dishes to try when asked! üôåüèªüôåüèª

Exciting eating place with varieties of Malaysia delights comparable with hawker standard of Pinang and Ipoh. Conveniently located in the neighbourhood heartland next to Yishun MRT station and bus interchange  at modern shopping mall Northpoint City. Love the prawn noodles and Ipoh noodles. Freshly prepared healthy ingridients with tender loving caring skillful cooking and professional warm services. Clean tidy orderly neighbourhood with aircond and spacious relaxing seats. Friendly cosy comfy welcoming ambience for romantic intimates groups students tourists expats locals visitors and families.
No fuss or frills authentic Hakka cuisine, at very affordable prices. Must come for anyone who loves genuine good food.
Awesome and delicious food at reasonable prices. Hidden place, sad to see it become too popular cause then we will need to queue haha. Support your local businesses!
Order was quick when you shared with them that you are in a hurry. The serving auntie was super nice today.

It's my go to place for mee soto. $4.50 serving gives a lot of chicken and one piece of begedil . Soup is favorful. Tonight I am lucky there is still chicken satay available. It's huge ... $0.70 each. Peanut sauce is not as chunky as other stalls.perhaps is end if day already.. Sad that mutton is sold out.  Normally the stalk close or sold out by 7pm.
super good jjajangmyeon!!!! the spicy fried chicken is good too! japchae is on the sweet side. love their kimchi too! portions are huge so good for groups, if not it would be too pricy per pax

I love their hor fun. Full of wok hei. Requested for pork lard to fry together with the hor fun. So shiokadoo.
Staff very friendly and helpful. Clean outlet.
Food taste great, portion is big and affordable. Waiting time is quite long during peak hours. Will definitely go again.

When I made a few sporadic visits for takeaway last year, the food standard for their regular dishes kind of dropped. During the Chinese New Year period the Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ was bland. However, last month's takeaway of their set menu was the best. All the dishes still taste good although it's a takeaway. The portions are big. Well worth the $48. My family polished off the food that night. But I have not tried their delivery service though.

ordered mixed grill ($22) and the portion was shockingly small compared to the ones served at other Collins outlets I've been to. Pork chop was much smaller than the size of my palm and chicken chop was obviously cut by a knife which reduced it to half its original portion

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Ordered from grab food duck rice and chicken noodle but the noodle inside got rice. And the sauce is dark sauce. Worst food I ever had.

Was just here today, on a Monday lunch hr. Store's open, ordered satay and mee rebus. Que was a little long as expected but satay was ready in 10 mins. Really yummy and juicy satay! Mee rebus was sumptuous as well ü§ó

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Pretty decent food and prices. Very good and quick service. Highball tower was a bit diluted,they added too much ice. If ordering ala-carte, please check cause they may miss out on some items/ give the wrong serving.
Toooooo pricey for the menu. Not worth it
Loved the food there. Especially the lontong
Food was good ordered their signature

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Shidah and Shariff have been wonderful while we are at Suki Suki Thai Safra Toa Payoh.
Food is fresh and tasty. Soup base was super refreshing especially Red Tom Yum. Thank you so much for the great service.
Unhealthy but delicious. Die Die Must try!  We are here again on September 25.  Delicious!
Ever since the change of staff, the food portion become smaller :/ Price stayed the same but still tastes more or less the same

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Food was amazing!!! ü§©

Really Good Western Food! Had the Ribeye 250gms at $16.80 inclusive of 2 side dishes. Good Quality Beef! Charred on the outside, juicy inside. Try Medium done. I had it Medium well which was a bit overdone but still a pretty good piece of Steak. Try it.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Ordered drunken chicken, fried rice,  sheng jian bao and they tasted quite bad, the standard in this branch is way below average of other branches. Not worth paying. I would take my money to other crystal jade outlets. Giving two star only coz egg white conpoy tasted ok.. You've been warned.
Quality drop to so so only. Guess they cannot cope with too many customers during peak.
Authentic Xing Hua foods. Affordable price and big portion.
Had chicken chop! The black pepper sauce and chicken is decent. The mash potato is quite horrible tho. But value for money! Old school western food.
Fries and Onion rings were soggy and cold. Tried toasting in the oven and unable to turn crispy. Onion rings tasted weird like plastic. Chicken chop thick coated by bread crumbs

One of the best prata (and curry) I've ever had, as well as very good service from ordering to tray collection. This is my go-to place for prata and I hope no one realises how good Prata Wala is so I won't need to queue.

One of the more popular Japanese resturant with Japanese at the west area

Serve quite an array of Japanese food here
They also give a good range of lunch sets

Therefore you won‚Äôt have any problem finding what you want to eat

Staffs also attentive to refill your drinks

I could have gone more of my yakitori but it was ok.

***If you like what I commented and wrote‚Ä¶
Join as my followers and let‚Äôs share life & food comments!!!***

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Spicy Spicy Spicy Great food and friendly staff. Will definitely come back more often.

It‚Äôs a new place located in North Spine near Lee Wee Nam library within NTU. Some of the best salad options with pasta or rice or potato base.

On an average it costs about 4-5SGD for a base +2 add ons with a salad sauce on a bed of lettuce. It‚Äôs worth visiting multiple times.

Proteins include tofu (2 types), chickpeas and veggies cover broccoli, corn, cucumber and tomato etc.

It‚Äôs handy for quick bites or takeaway!
Nice place with nice Japanese foods

1. Ordered salmon belly sashimi but only 1 piece out of the 3 pieces is the real salmon belly sashimi (you can see the difference in the photo)
2. Avocado maki was poorly wrapped with the seaweed falling apart (in the photo also)
3. The worst is the char siew ramen!!! 1 taste of the soup and it's exactly the seasoning from myojo chicken instant noodles!! Any decent ramen chef will take pride in their soup base as it's like the soul of the ramen!
Try it at your own risk cos it's definitely not worth your money! This is my first & last time ordering!
Nice malaysia food. Food court style. Self service.
Ordered takeaway on 7 Nov and got home to realise the wrong order given to me. I paid more and got less. Disappointing.

maggie goreng combo $8.90 - MUTTON IS COLD !!
soup tulang $5 - tasty but salty .
didn't expect much for the services . initially wanted to order tulang merah 3 piece $7 (only 1 person is eating) but they kept on pushing us to buy 5 piece $11 ... and even ask "ENOUGH IS IT?" "WHY the rest never eat tulang merah" even after informing CAN'T eat !!
and when i decided to eat soup tulang instead , the person's face who took our order changes . try not to push your "food selling" too hard when customer doesn't want to eat it . no second time at this rest.

$1 nasi lemak. Can you beat that? Although the serving portion is not huge, it can be a full meal for most people. Not comparable to those nasi lemak with otah, fried chicken wings and sambal tempeh, as you get to choose either fried fish or ikan bilis.

Have it as a snack in between meal, the portion is right size that you can squeeze it in between meal time.

Went to Jurong Point's outlet on a Sunday. Was my 1st time and probably the last. My family of 6 were not let in to the restaurant when there's clearly an unoccupied table for 6 there. Had to talk to the worker and reason with him as to why he couldn't let us sit at that table. His reason being that table is too close to other tables (safety distancing measures) but all other occupied tables with customers seated are close to each other too. It made no sense and the worker finally let us sit there only when we said that we would like to speak to the manager about this matter. Upon sitting at the table, we were not given the menu after a good 5 minutes and had to approach the waiter to be given the menu. The waiter told us that the order is to be done via scanning a QR code but the QR code slip was not given to us. We were cluelessly finding the QR inside the menu when it was actually a printed QR code slip which is supposed to be given by the waiter. So we had to ask for the menu and also the QR code to be given to us. The food arrived fast but the soup tasted bland. Even the soup with the "richest" taste option selected tasted bland. The soup was barely warm too, not hot like a soup that is freshly cooked. The only thing that was nice were the onsen eggs.  Basically an unpleasant experience going there.
The signature bee hoon taste good, goes with the special gravy. Nice ambience, lake view

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: A dim sum place that is near home. The variety is not bad with many of the dum sum dishes to be available. However, the taste is just normal street standard. No crowd at 10am on Friday morning, pretty relaxing for me.
The naan is good quality, the mamak is friendly!
Not crowded but crowds starts to build after 7pm. Food taste are okay but the price is steep for out of town area.
Typical hawker food court and the lontong is good

Food standard & prices same as before. Only thing is staff service & attitude must improve. Need to go for basic service quality course if possible. Young guy at cashier counter with attitude, need to improve his service & manners. Miss the warm feeling of last time when the male boss at dinning hall talking to customers. Don‚Äôt expect much of service quality but at least the basic from them but that also don‚Äôt have. Ts is my honest opinion.
GREAT FOOD GREAT AMBIENCE GREAT PLACE GREAT STAFF! Worth every penny! Foods are delicious! WOULD DEFO COME BACK!!!! ü§ó

Ordered:
- grilled pork which has the very good balance of the fats and meat. I absolutely love this and will definitely come back for this (only if I‚Äôm forgoing my diet üòÇ)
- clear Tom yum which has a mild sour  and spicy taste. Felt that i might enjoy it more if it‚Äôs more sour and spicy as it tastes just mehhhhh. Lots of squids, fish and mushroom tho!
- omelette crab where the egg was very very fluffy yet crispy on the outer. But I can‚Äôt taste the flavour of crab and I had this dish thinking it‚Äôs just plain egg (my cousin said it will be better to order the prawn omelette so that u can see the prawn meat)
- pad Thai tasted like the normal pad Thai (honestly can someone share with me how a plate of amazing pad Thai should taste? With wokhey??? üòÇüòÇüòÇ)
- kailan which tasted quite clean yet doesn‚Äôt have the glassy taste (if you are like me who hates vegetables, this is a perfect option for you cos it doesn‚Äôt have the vegetables taste üòÇ)
- Thai green tea had a very strong pandan taste and normal Thai iced tea was a little sweet (but I like it) and has the dry tea after taste (which I believe is normal to have)

Ambience was good, but it‚Äôs not enticing enough that would bring me back so 3 stars especially since food was decent

Came for their dim sum today and was really authentic and good. Service was quite fast despite an almost full house. Their steamed pork ribs is a must try. Ample parking at the HDB carpark. A good choice to spend your weekend morning.

Nice Chinese seafood restaurant with good and prompt service. Offers Al fresco dining as well. Tried the crispy pork and roast duck and they were above expectations. Otherwise other dishes like chili crab were good but not great.
The mee rebus is outstanding. Love the mee Soto too

Chef Cash was extraordinary with this exquisite meal. Value for money Omakase in the west definitely! The meal set also comes with Sake.

Our love is the four gras, otoro and their unique seafood tofu with generous portion of ikura. Completely fulfilling meal and money well spent. Extremely wallet friendly Japanese food within TungLok.

This was quite an unusual experience. Yunnan cuisine. Not sure if it‚Äôs authentic but it‚Äôs different from usual. I had the minced meat and salted veg soupy noodles plus set meal. Minced meat reminded me of zhajiang mian minced meat. Bowl was huge but mostly just soup. Soup was mild to medium spicy. But had the salted vegetable taste. Not bad. Egg was kind of hard and dry. I guess it‚Äôs their style. Different from the Japanese style. Dessert was a bit like ice jelly without ice. Not too sweet.

Always no stock of something, drink, ricebucket or original chicken

Bad and slow service, no answer phone calls
I ordered F2 Blackened Cajun Fish. Wow the fish was extremely saltish. Had to down my drink to dilute the saltiness. Worse Fish & Chips I had üëé

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Old school traditional teochew cuisine. Pricey but I think the quality of ingredients and mastery in the cooking makes it worth.

Good to come as a family to celebrate special occasions. Please get the fried sea cucumber and fried pork rib you will not regret it!
Friendly..staff

This place makes Sushi Express feel like an artisan sushi restaurant. Food is slow to serve and sushi looks pathetic. Sashimi dont look fresh and is unappealing. Better off with other options. Worse sushi place I been to in my life.

First time to visit this thai eatery located in Toa Payoh North. Many google reviewers warned about their portion size, I agree quite big, for 4 pax no problem.

Ordered Thai steamed fish with lime, promo price of $12.90. We also ordered plain omelette ($7, some cabbage in it), basil stir fry pork, fishcake ($9 soft inside, like otah filling), kai lan with slated fish ($7) and 4 plates of white rice, total bill $46.90.

A hearty dinner in the neighborhood that is wallet friendly.
Friendly staff and tasty food! Sesame chicken is the bestüòã
Loved the Ayam Masak Merah üëçüèª
Both the naan n prata are good. Chicken curry also good.

I had beef rib eye cubed Don. Though the portion is adequate, I loved the grilled meat, not too dry or raw wet, and it was so good.It is priced reasonably well compared with other Japanese eateries in Singapore.

Lady Boss is menopausal. Or maybe woke up on the wrong side of bed. Bad lousy attitude, and refused to give more chilli packs when we requested. Fries were too salty and dry. Disappointing, not worth the calories. Will never patronize again.

Now with this covid situation, hope they close shop better if want to continue service and quality like this.
Food was decent. Beef redang was above average in my opinion but pricing is expensive. 1 piece of beef with 2 portions of brinjal came to $7. Not good enough to warrant a repeat.

BTK has a name for itself, for good reasons. Fragrant rice and tender chicken, perfectly cooked and chilled which left it juicy and gelatinous. Fried tofu was also a surprisingly good dish - soft and silky inside, with a crispy and lightly salted skin. Avoid their coffee ribs, until they do something about it - we all had one bite and left the dish alone for good reason, it was both too sweet and too bitter, the coffee and sugar flavours did not merge successfully and left an awkward aftertaste.

Excellent yakitori, the food is straightforward such as pork belly, chicken, chicken cheese balls on sticks but unlike most stalls selling such food it is dipped in sticky BBQ sauce. Good value, basically the same as Old Chang Kee but I find Wadori is better. Does value meals or you can just order whatever you like.

Awesome Malaysia foods.  Reasonably priced and the standards of most stalls are consistent in all the Malaysia Boleh foodcourts in Singapore. The dried chilli ban main is definitely worth mentioning. The handmade noodles are chewy and very Q. Not the soggy sort. The sauce and chilli combo is just right. The addition of soft boiled egg further enhances the smoothness of the noodles. The ikan bilis are fried to perfection. Crispy and not salty at all. As usual, the foodcourt is packed with patrons from 3-5pm (weekdays) during their coffee and tea promo. Only 50 cents a cup! Highly recommend if your are craving for some authentic good old Malaysian dishes.
Excellent Nasi padang! Hidden gem!

Mentaiko Salmon Don is terrible taste. Overpriced too.. if taste is good then price will be acceptable. But taste is low quality, no standard. Mentaiko sauce like machiam mayonnaise. Don't waste your time ordering Mentai Salmon Don. Add mentai sauce (mayonnaise taste) for $2 not worth it also. It would be ok if the taste is good. Unagi is decent and taste good for $12. Recommend to go shopping mall eat better, aircon, cheaper, taste better. Only wanted to support local but the result is disappointing. Enjoy your meal. STAY away from their fake "mentai sauce'

My fave for the past two decades.
Simply one of the best in sg.
Although the price is simply becoming one of the priciest in sg, easily $6+ for 1 meat 2 veg.
It is now a luxury food, not sustainable to eat it even twice a week.
This was my worst experience with Jack's Place tpy. Food presentation was bad. Cake is in mini size & so dry.

I tried the mutton rendang. The rice itself wasn‚Äôt that fragrant. Ingredient and spices were limited. The curry dip was disappointing. Almost no taste. Vegetables were bland too. Only saving the grace was the mutton. It was tasty with a heavy dose of thick yoghurt. Teh tarik is not bad too.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
It would be better if I didn‚Äôt hv to queue for that long. Their signature are all indicated in the pictures that r posted on menu.
Mine is beef noodles. Beef texture is like a bit hard but seasoning wise is okay for me. Maybe could use some salts.

Another favorite place of mine to taste Malaysia foods. When I come to Northpoint, 90% of the time I will have my meal here as the foods here are very affordable compared to other food outlets.

Not all their foods are great, so you need to choose wisely. My favorite foods here are chilli ban mee (noodles) and char kuey teow. The popiah, nasi lemak, penang hokkien mee (prawn mee) are so so only.

If you come during meal time, it will be very crowded and you need to share places with others. My advice is come early or choose odd times to come here, so you won't be frustrated with all the fully occupied places.

Hands down one of the best western food out here in singapore, possibly the best in Ang Mo Kio. The chicken was cooked to perfection with the meat being both tender and juicy, you wouldn‚Äôt think any chicken thigh could be this good. Cherry on the top, the skin was crispy bare in mind it was takeaway. Definitely coming back for more chicken.
Although the food selections not much but it's enough that if you want to have a meal. Food tasted quite ordinary.
The foods here delicious n good. The staffs polite n helpful. Peking duck is superb. Highly recommended.
Mentai Chicken.. Nice food

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
Very crowded, we did the right thing to book in advance forces Sunday. It was full house.
The marinate meat were nice. Service staffs were attentive and fast. Good and spicy chilli with choice of non spicy dip too.

The best indian food in town. Home cook style food.  The prawn & Chicken Satti Sorru (Claypot Indian Style)  & prawn sothi  (Prawn lemak)  & crab rasam was awesome! Super service! Better make reservation on weekends!
Decent tze char with lovely signature food and slow braised pork belly

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Been here twice... Good food & service:)
The prata and curry is normal , nothing fanastic

Very pleasant eatery, run by ultra-friendly husband-and-wife team, offers wide array of local delights. Highlights include Fish Head Steamboat, Braised Belly Pork and Prawn Roll. All nicely prepared in hygienic conditions. We support and well recommend.
A family friendly outlet with open ceiling, a nostalgic ambience with rock stars photos on the wall, menu valued for money and friendly staff that makes a heartful satisfied dinner of the day!
Where else can you find a simple and good $1 nasi lemak! Of course you can top up with other food and pay more. The owner and workers are both friendly and food reasonably tasty.
New Andy's Grill opened here and is worth trying.****

Went with 5 people, waiter did not clarify and ordered the 6 pax set meal when we intended to get the 4 pax one. Aircon spoilt and it was hot inside. Was celebrating birthday and waiter offered longevity bun, did not mention it was chargeable and I ordered it thinking it was complimentary. Food was not nice and overpriced for $400
So so... Egg prata is big on surface area... But thin. MyBriyani House and even my nearby prata is better.
Nice foods, i like very much
Steak don and salmon aburi don are best here. Steak is high quality for affordable price. The only thing is wait time is too long unless you order a takeaway.
nice prata and Indian Muslim style stir fried cooked food. I love the Maggie Mee Goreng too!
Went around 8pm on a sat and still had a slight queue but didn't have to wait long. Good plate of old school western food. Nothing special though.
Really enjoyed the food here, especially the xin hua bee hoon and marinated cockles.
Served cold stale choco pie. Asked about it and they say they don't heat it up before serving or smth LOL

Awesome service by cute cute plum boy wearing a spec. He is an asset of the restaurant.
Very tasty food with reasonable price. Will come back again

The meat was marinated perfectly with the sauce and easily to be cooked.
I do not like to eat beef but their beef is tender and tasted nicely with the lime sauce.
Worth a try and definitely will come back again.

Very nice place for value for money grill. It is located in a coffee shop. The place is very casual and relax atmosphere. There are a few other stalls in this coffee shop.
Ordered a ribeye steak in black pepper sauce at a good price. It is nicely done and comparable to those restaurant standard. Also ordered the lamb shank. Not too bad for that price.
Overall it is a wonderful experience. Definitely great value for the price and I will be back if I need a steak fix in a casual manner.

We booked several tables for an event and ordered the food well before hand. We were at the restaurant at 6.30pm. At 9.00pm, some of the dishes are still not served. Food too too long to arrive. Best to skip this place if you want to host a successful dinner event. Food is nice, but just not worth the time and effort.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Definitely a must if you're in northern part of Singapore. Not only are the pratas made fresh upon arrival, they also have vegetarian gravy to cater to vegans. Awesome dalcha also
Amazing breakfast and service
Amazing seafood at affordable prices. Do pre-order your black pepper and chilli crab!
Good for a quick snack, situated close to the bus stop and MRT.
Ordered hanjuku egg. As first , I rejected as it looked like a cooked egg. Then they served again as picture .. is this hanjuku eggs? complaining only for their hanjuku egg . Funny hanjuku egg

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Not that pricey and like eating mookata under air conditioning environment more important is they had exhaust over the table that help to minimise the smoky smell.

Great porridge with a variety of choices including porridge with black chicken!

Apr 2022: another visit and porridge is as good as first visit.

Apr 2022: yet another visit in the same month! This time I tried the pumpkin porridge base and it was good! I think I got one of the last bowls and so the porridge was thick and yummy!

Although limited variety but it serves its purpose as a Japanese Food court.
What I like best is you can just scan the QR code on each table to access to each stall to order.
You only need to leave the table when food is ready.üëçüëçüëç

Generally very very oily food; standard has dropped a lot.

The beef soup noodles- in the menu pic, the beef portions look ‚Äòsubstantial or decent portions‚Äô but when it came, it only had three skillet pieces!!!  And it was not cheap!!

The dried ‚Äòspring rolls‚Äô were gooey, which I understand that‚Äôs their norm but it was incredibly oily.

Personally the steamed dumplings skin was a bit on the thick side.

Oh yea the deep fried tau sar pau was truly truly oily and the tau sar portions were so pathetic‚Ä¶ and did I say oily ?
As was the deep fried dumplings‚Ä¶. Both had thick portions of skin.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Crystal jade jiangnan specialises in la mien and does it well. The menu also includes some cantonese cuisine and dim sum.  Some lovely dishes that I would go back for more would by the seafood crispy noodles and multi grain fried rice and the xiao long bao. The chunky seafood with its gravy was thoughtfully set aside to prevent the crispy noodles from turning soft too quickly. I like generous chunks of fish squid mushrooms prawns and a dash of leafy green that made this dish a seafood haven. It was well executed without being overly salty. That goes the same for the multi grain brown rice that was well cooked and presented in a stone bowl. Absolutely delicious and very healthy indeed! They have a spread of various types of xiaolong bao but I would recommend the normal flavour that allows you to experience the delicate yet flavorful pork infused with a delicious broth and sealed within the dumpling.  I wasn't too impressed with the lao sao bao which had very little filling making it rather dry;  and the ying yang steamed dumpling that had the skin too thick and the filling devoid of flavour. Service is alright though it would be ideal to make reservations if the group is large due to the small seating area.

This is the second time in a row prata wala has got my order wrong. I ordered takeaway so I didn‚Äôt realize until I got home. Terrible, especially since I paid more than the food I got. One of the times they even gave me briyani when I ordered prata. The receipt is on the bag. But they just anyhow pack the food inside. Such a disappointment after waiting so long for the food.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Delicious Singapore style chicken rice (roasted and white). Free soup served with the meals. Also ordered the cereal prawn dish which was crunchy and delicious. Come on weekdays, reservations needed for Friday and weekends. Good for large groups.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Paper dosa not bad, but a bit oily. Mango lassi superb!

Had dinner here. Chicken and vegetables were ok, but sweet and sour pork was terrible! No pieces of meat at all, just pork fats and flour crumbs, see photo! Tiny pieces, not a single proper piece of meat. We gave feedback, was told their boss said that "their sweet and sour pork is like that one, is all fats one, no meat, that's the way they cook."

Ridiculous! Shame on them. Never order their sweet and sour pork, such a disappointment.
Impressive and interesting mala collagen soup! Thai Green Milk Tea is good too (forgot to take picture) Will be back again :)

Best place for Indian food in ang mo kio,
Milagu Pongal only available on Tuesday and Friday

Samosa stuffing is very healthy
Vadai is cheaper

I can imagine the fuss with wanting to taste nostalgia. Other than that, I'll say,  take your money elsewhere. We were there on a weekday evening and there were about 5-6 customers ahead of us in the queue. We got to order in about 10 minutes and I'd have to commend the kitchen for delivering at such record speed. After ordering, we waited for about 8 minutes before our orders were ready. The Mushroom Sauce Chicken Chop ($6.50) had a piece of flabby skin that was not charred to extract at least 30% of the fat. It was just cooked and not actually the way I prefer to eat my chicken skin. The piece of chicken, although tender and juicy, had quite a fowl-like odour which reminded me of chicken chops at cook houses. I have no idea how this store used to taste like, but I do not like their style of cooking now. Fries were just tasteless, not salty and blah. The slice of bread although nicely toasted, had the taste of Planta which I hate. The Grilled Salmon ($9) was under seasoned with a strong fishy taste but the doneness was just right. It was soft within and melted in the mouth, not overdone and flaky at all. The worst of the lot would have to be the Butter Garlic Lamb Chops ($12). We got a sinewy cut of the meat and the butter garlic compound was an absolute horror. It was made of Planta margarine and dried rosemary..nothing in it had the taste of butter or garlic! All in all, it's great if you miss the taste of 90's style western food at an inflated price. Otherwise, it's just cheap ingredients, canned beans and junk sold at a premium price. I could walk over to the coffeeshop next door and get a chicken chop at $5. Perhaps our taste buds have evolved and we're now spoilt for choices when it comes to customizable fancy sides like sauteed mushrooms, roasted sweet potatoes, mac n cheese and the like.

Economical Japanese foods. Foods are well presented and value for money especially the value set meal. Just that the fried squids are over fried and oily. And not forgetting the staffs are friendly and nice at this outlet.

Tims is a very cozy little restaurant serving nice western food. The staff here is nice and friendly. Food is always consistently good. Generous portions for what we refer to as neighbourhood price. I recommend their chicken cutlet - crunch on the outside but juicy on the inside. Their steak and seafood on specials are often good too.

After eating the prawn mee here, you will not want to eat any other prawn mee! I sometimes even have cravings for the prawn mee here! I love the dry version, which comes with dried deshelled prawns. (Will add extra vinegar) It comes with a bowl of soup at the side, which I will pour into my dry noodles when I'm almost done with my meal, mixing the soup with the sauces of the dry noodle. So I get best of both worlds! If u prefer fresh prawns, order the soup version and peel the prawn shell yourself. Haha. OK. I'm drooling now...
They also serve lor mee
AND a mix of both lor mee and prawn mee in 1 dish of u can't decide which to have and can't finish 2 bowls on your own.
Boss lady advised to call to check if you want dry version later part of the day, as the dried prawn always sold out early.

content: Food was super taste and i enjoy the meals

If you're a Thai food lover then I urge you to not missed out this authentic Thai food stall that is hidden right in the heart of toa payoh central. I have seen this stall around recently as it was opened not long ago after covid period. I think around May if I'm not wrong? The main chef is from Thailand so please be assured you're getting real authentic Thai food! This stall is located right in J99 coffeeshop together my favourite chicken rice stall... I have been eating chicken rice all along and haven't been able to try this Thai stall until today.

Their menu is very extensive and it all the usual Thai favourites can be found right in their menu. Their price are also super affordable and most of all, it is very very valuable for money. Basil pork goes for 5.50 and it comes with egg. You can also try out their basil prawn which is super good as well. Their prawns are not those small little shrimps as they used medium prawns which are fresh and crunchy.

The aunties here are also super friendly and courteous so don't be afraid to ask for their recommendations if you're a first timer like me. I will be back again to try their other dishes such as phad Thai and Tom yum soup. Hope they will survive in the long run as this stall is quite small and if you don't look around carefully, you might missed their stall as there are quite a nunber of stall in this coffeeshop.
