content:
12th March 2022 (Saturday) - 3pm

The middle-age lady cashier tilted the sushi box sideway when putting into plastic bag which caused the sushi to toppled and is quite unfriendly over the whole payment duration.

Definitely need more training.

Good Prata (kosong) and garlic, not so tasty kway tiao goreng, nice fish curry. There is air-con, and service was pleasant and waiting time was reasonable. Pratas were served fresh, crispy and tasty, unlike many prata places which prepare a truckload of pratas and become soggy by the time it arrives on our plates. Overall a pleasant experience!

Dropped by this place for Chong Qing grilled fish and was not disappointed. The fish and sauce is really really nice! We had the È¶ôËæ£ soup based and added a few sides. The servings of the sides are really generous. Much much more generous than the famous Tan Yu imo. I will definitely drop by again for their MLXG next time! And, having robot waitress to serve the dishes is so innovative and cute!

Their mee rebus has a nostalgic taste to it, reminded me of my childhood. It is competently prepared but it falls short of being outstanding. Very reasonably priced at $2.50.
The chicken wing is well seasoned with aromatic spices at $1.50.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: It was quite disappointing as the sides I ordered, the mash potatoes isn‚Äôt seasoned with butter or even salt, it just plain potatoes, the Mac and cheese has close to no salt either, likewise for the unseasoned chicken which they barely pass it off with a hickory bbq sauce. I didn‚Äôt remember Aston standards to be this low as it was a place that I would go to in my younger years. The standard of their food has certainly deteriorate over the years. Would not visit again, as western food from coffee shops would be better than this.

Their standards have dropped massively. The chicken briyani was very generic and lacked taste. The mee goreng has no wokhey and tastes of simple tomato sauce and not much else. We have been going to this place for 5 years, but this may be our last time.
Worth the money..

Food are terrible.
Not authentic at all
Food was alright, though there are more value-for-money bowls of a similar standard elsewhere! üç±
Food is tasty and price is fair. Please improve the ventilation so that patrons do not leave the place with smelly clothes, the smell is noticeable after entering to Dabao.

Ordered seabass with tomyam coconut milk, basil leaf minced pork, pineapple fried rice and mango salad.

Pineapple Fried Rice: Extreme Failure.
Serving was huge, but the rice was extremely soggy. Absolutely not fragrant nor tasty.

Fish: Fail.
Even with the fire below, the entire dish was luke warm at most. Fish was very bland and coconut milk tomyam was just looking it's part without tasting like it at all.

Mango Salad: Fail.
Was sour as expected but totally lacking the spicy touch.

Minced Pork: Pass.
The ONLY dish which saved the day.for them.

Won't return.

I have been ordering through Grabfood many times. Can say their food is not consistent at all. Overall, their grilled fish is still passable, but both their mushroom soup and mash potato taste bad (really sour) and the garlic bread lacks flavour. Gotta improve on their side dishes.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
I would give 6 stars if I could. This place is mind blowing good. I guess it‚Äôs the curry fish curry and chicken rice rice combo for me. Everything else was the supporting cast because those 2 just stole the show in my mouth.

Nonetheless I enjoyed every other dish as well. Will be back if I have curry fish head and chicken rice cravings!

I ordered the striploin steak through food panda, i usually dont write reviews but i was cery happy with my meal. It came with a nice portion of rice, steak was pretty food and fries wont too bad. Overall it cost me $11 and that is pretty affordable. Highly reccomend trying it out

Fantastic meal here at A-Roy Thai. Was a Sunday night around 8+ but the restaurant was still bustling, will recommend to make a reservation if you come during the peak dinner timings.

The meal itself was delightful, not the regular local style Thai food but according to my gf, it had more Northern Thai influences to it but more importantly, done well.

Prices are not cheap, 1 appetizer, 3 mains and 2 drinks set us back around $90+ compared to the regular Thai food places but this is money well spent.

The lemongrass salad was fantastic, a must order (the staff don't tell you but you eat it with the wrap on the side). Tom yum kung was good, not mind blowing but definitely above average. The Grilled Pork was done very differently, in a good way, a spicier way actually.

The service was friendly and the food came out surprisingly fast. The grilled pork took a bit longer but the rest of the dishes came first.

Would definitely return! But have to budget myself else it'd really burn a huge hole in my pocket!

Soup restaurant is situated inside United Square mall in Novena area. We have 4 adults seated inside the corner cubicle. Their famous chicken, tofu and sea cucumbers with mushrooms are recommended. Their soups are slightly salty. Overall we enjoy a good dinner there.
Good South Indian food. Been here many times. Friendly staffs.  Parking space hard to find because of MRT construction.
Ordered in through Foodpanda. Maggie Goreng was tastless. Not sure if they deserve the 2 stars even.

The food is amazing, but the service is bad. The lady at the cashier, short hair very rude. She saw customer standing at the counter, never bother at all. And purposely act busy arranging glasses. Even after see also never approach. Imagine people want to buy food when they are hungry, this is how you guys treat?  We are not coming there for free food, to be treated like that.

Very affordable prices. Portion is big and not stingy on the meat. Butter chicken was so flavourful and was really unique because of the smokiness.
The lamb shank was really tender and flavourful. Loved it. Palak paneer was good too although I would have liked it if the spice was stronger.
Staff totally and intentionally ignored customers despite us keeping saying hello to get her attention to get seats. Staff name is Catherine.
Loved the scramble eggs and fried lotus root. ‰∏≠Ëæ£ not that spicy

Didn't manage to reserve a booking.
Took awhile to get seated on a Friday night.
Be it cooked food or fresh food, all are great!

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Friendly staff and good food.
power mee rebus is good. the mee rebus ok, but the power add on : chicken egg and satay sauce is great.
The food was good and staff are really helpful! Food is also VERY reasonably priced especially with the Safra discount! Will come here again with friends & family.

They deep dry the potatoes and lotus roots, which makes the dish really good. It smells amazing and I can't wait to dig in from the takeaway box.

HOWEVER, usually good things come with certain level of screwed ups right. That's the case for me. I ordered a mala soup take away and I was given a dry mala instead. When I approached the counter they told me no more soup available. Perhaps they can let me know earlier.

Also during dinner time it is better not to come later than 7pm to avoid the same disappointment and the long waiting hours. Yep, I waited for 1 hour for the take away.

A friend ordered for my birthday lunch via Foodpanda. Unfortunately, the tuna was sour, the salmon was acceptable but tasted slightly dodgy. Not a fan of the chosen rice. Also, gave me food poisoning. Not sure if the restaurant did not pack it well or the ingredients were not fresh or the food delivery person screwed up.

But when the food came, it was just in a normal bento box as pictured, no dry ice or anything to keep it cool. Weather wasn't very hot, and food panda only delivers within 3 to 5 km?

Had 4 courses of charcoal to get it out of my system üò≠üò≠.

Had a pleasant birthday dinning experience. Food is great (not too salty). Particularly liked the yellow croaker fish, which is very fresh and tender. The service staff went the extra mile to play the birthday song and sang birthday wishes with us. They also gave us a free fruit platter.
They‚Äôve got the best honey lemon tart.

This is a small shop I've been to recently. Chongqing spicy grilled fish, double-cooked pork, shredded cabbage, etc. are all good. Basically, according to the local tastes, the dishes are salty and oily, but they are delicious and the prices are very reasonable. With a bottle of ice and snowflakes, that's it. . . You may have to wait for a table during meal times.

Excellent no-fuss affordable Japanese food in a homely setting. I love the dashi stock being used and the miso soup was not overly salty, yet very flavourful.

Lower Pierce reservoir is round the corner; very scenic, plenty of monkeys and good for a stroll albeit very humid.

It was full house when I was there. Will visit again.

Clean and neat Indian restaurant near spring leaf nature park. The coin prata was one of the best we had recently. They also serve different variety of thosai. The oothappam we had was good. Overall good selection if you are a meat and fish lover.

Exceptionally clean and good service
The environment is comfortable and elegant, the meals are medium-level, the price is medium-high, and a comfortable place to chat and enjoy meals. Open until 10.45pm

There is no prior booking of table for lunch or dinner. Need to register and will given a queue number. Waiting time about 20 to 30 minutes depending on the crowd on that day.  While waiting you can choose your dish from the given menu list. This queue system is very good. Place is cosy and clean. The service is good and food serve very fast. We like the fried rice with chicken meat which is thick and plenty. Will come again with family.

At B2 of AMK hub, same level as ntuc fairprice.

Many choices of local n malaysian food at reasonable pricing compared to other eateries in the mall.

Went in the afternoon at about 1. 30pm, quite crowded but was able to find a seat within 10mins.

Economical rice- About 20-30 different dishes to choose from.. The veg n meat we chose were delicious. $6.50

Fish soup- Ordered double fish soup. Soup is tasty, fish was also fresh. Opted to add milk.. $8

Would love to come back again to try other food.

Food was decent. But there was a fight among the staff during peak period lunch time. Fighting was pretty loud. Partly due to the overwhelming orders both walk-in customers and food delivery orders.

The worst part was that I overheard the kitchen staff telling one of the staff to inform the customer to get their food while calling the customers ÁôΩÁó¥ (idiots).

Note: it‚Äôs a self service restaurant which people might not know and the self service counter is all the way at the back.

This incident occurred on Sunday, 10/04/2022,  1.45pm.

Was having lunch here yesterday n specifically check with stall their opening time n was told Mon to Thur until 4pm, rest on Friday ONLY!
I just went to buy but don't have again. Guess will just strike it off my list

Place has gone thru some reno, and signs of more reno being done, with the addition of some new shops. Today ordered food from Ya Long. Not disappointed. The white beehoon, veg dishes were all so good. Definitely will visit again to check out the new stores
amazing service staff thums up!!!! all my food arrived timely and the chawanmushi is better than sushiro! queue is long as expected but it was all worth it

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Food is just about average. Some dishes with interesting presentations but otherwise quite normal tasting, normal portion but double the usual zhi char price. Food serving and timing was bad even though there were only 5 tables other than ‚Ä¶

Easily the best chicken Briyani I have had in Singapore. The mutton and fish curry is especially tasty. A great find near Sembawang and we will be sure to come back again! Absolutely delicious and great dining experience.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Visited yesterday first time, food is gud but little pricy, especially filter coffee is very nice, thank you for the gud coffee
Steam fish was very good, ok for others such as tang hoon salad (too spicy, suggest to deliberately say low low spice if you wish), 'deep fried pork with rice' is ok, rice was rather hard.

I have ordered from this restaurant for the past 2 weeks through food panda. The food was quite tasty even though for some reason they always change my order due to having not enough stock on hand... especially the baked beans... Apparently no baked beans for the past week but its still listed in foodpanda...

Today i ordered again and the coleslaw tasted awful, very sour and presumably expired... I took the first bite and threw it away. The few times i ordered coleslaw from them, it tasted normal... but not today.

I hope that the restaurant does not keep food overnight and serve them to customers the next day... this poses a health risk.

I will probably still order from them again... but never the coleslaw after this event.

‚ÄúOne cannot think well, love well, sleep well, if one has not dined well.‚Äù
This review was made possible by my HEX Crypto stakes. Hex.com

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content:
Service: 5/5
Service staff are very attentive and friendly. They are patient when explaining their dishes. Thumbs up to their service manager.

Food: 1/5
1. Mushroom Tofu
Probably the better dish but they are a seafood restaurant?
2. Shark Fin Soup
Generous portion of shark Fin but the soup was a disappointment
3. Dancing Roasted Chicken
It was fine, not great.
4. Salted Egg Crab
Honestly, this was what I was looking forward to - the sauce and crab were not in the same building; disappointing.
5. Opeh Leaves vermicelli
Really big time disappointment. the vermicelli had a strange taste.

Ambience: 3/5
A nice place in the evening. quite cooling.

Price: 2/5
For the price you pay, you should get better food.

Final Verdict: Don't bother.
Prata n teh tarik is reasonably good. Only service is a little slow even when there's no crowd.

Food mediocre, yet had to wait an unreasonable amount of time for the food to be served. Coin prata came within 10 mins of ordering, which was reasonable. However, later on we had to remind them that we had another 2 dishes that weren‚Äôt served. Furthermore, the chicken briyani was already cooked and shouldn‚Äôt take so long to serve. However, that wasn‚Äôt the worst part, we ordered at 1527 and the ikan bilis white bee Hoon was only served at 1402. Everyone else had already eaten finish and only then had it been served which is absolutely ridiculous. Additionally, it seems as though the oil they used to cook the beehoon was reused as there was a rather strong odour.
One of the best prawn noodle in AMK central. Everyone must give it a try!

A dining place you must try if you are near macpherson.All their dishes are delicious and value for money.
üëçüëçüëçüëçüëçüëç
Cheap food but service abit slow resulted in long q in the morning before 8 to 9 am
Wonderful host.. cosy place
Excellent fluffy prata served with choice of mutton/fish curry, dalcha and my fav sambal ikan bilis (anchovies)

Opening on 4th Dec 2020,
One of the best Halal Hokkaido Ramen in town. Try it if you haven‚Äôt.

A long wait for food on a weekday evening but it was worth it as I had gained an appetite by then. The chicken was flavoured well and grilled with a slight char. The generous side dish of ratatouille was hearty and made up for the wait.
‚Äî-
Came back another time and ordered takeaway. Ordered the grilled fish of the day (sea bass) and beef brisket. The fish was fresh and the beef was tender and the beef fat melts in the mouth. Order the mash, it‚Äôs really yum. üëçüèº

Food deserves 5 ‚≠êÔ∏è, but be prepared to wait.
Melts in my mouth. Mizayaki beef.

Curry puffs crusts are very thick but crispy. Enj√≤yed the different types of dried bee hoon like satay, plain white, mee siam and Laksa. Drink are also available together with other finger food such as fish balls, held together by a stick.

The service is excellent. Truly appreciate that the staff keep refilling the tea in our glass. The fish is fresh. Food is delicious. The roasted meat is nice but slightly hard. I have a wonderful lunch time. Thank you!

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Back here two years after leaving Singapore. Wee Nam Kee used to be my go to local chicken rice place. I came here almost 2-3 times a week even even try were still up in their old location.

Yesterday we ordered all the good stuff I remembered and taste as well as quality wise they are still keeping up their same high level as ever before.

To my favorites belong obviously the roasted chicken, the chicken rice, their sweet and sour pork, baby kaylan with garlic and the mapo eggplant dish. All of which were support delicious. I don't know why we didn't order the bbq chashu as I remember that being fabulous too but I guess we already had more than enough food.

Wee Nam Kee still my favorite.

I have to say the food here is super inconsistent.

My first time ordering:
Got their beef donburi with broccoli, salmon Miso soup and mentaiko sauce.
Beef was good as it had flavourful and wasn't too dry. Broccoli we're kinda disappointing as it was just plain broccoli boiled in water and there were only 2 pieces. For the salmon Miso soup, it tasted good without being overly salty. Mentaiko sauce is spicier that your regular mentaiko and somehow the mentaiko is milder.
Overall I enjoyed my meal and this taste better than Yoshinoya if you need comparison. I also like how their portion is slightly larger.

Update: I ordered another 3 more times from them so a total of 4 times on 4 different days.

For my 2nd order I was super impressed. They added more seaweed to their don And the flavours were good. Only sad thing was the onsen egg with the broken yolk. But other than that it was a wonderful meal.

For my 3rd order, it was HORRIBLE, just look at the pictures attached. The rice was just lump together and mushy. How could they actually serve such rice to their customers? The boiled egg though perfectly cooked was just roughly handle, look at the broken egg white. For the protein this time, I got their wagyu flank beef and boy was that a mistake. Tough, flavourless piece of meat with some parts having some black pepper taste. For the price I was charged, I am SUPER DISAPPOINTED with this meal

For my 4th order which was during the week dine-in was allowed, I decided to give them another chance. Let me say I TOTALLY regretted my choice. Rice was AGAIN lumpy and mushy but this time it wasn't that bad only like 1/2 of the rice had this issue. This was during dinner time. What is wrong with them? Can't they even get the basic right anymore? Also I got the SALMON soup which this time apparently didn't contain any SALMON. Instead, was replaced with a small cube of tofu and a lot of kelp.

Hope they can really look into it and be consistent in their execution. My first 2 experience were great but the 3rd one and 4th just left be disappointed. Honestly if that was the first bowl that I had, I would have never chosen to order from them ever again. I don't know if their standards are dropping or if I'm ordering at very bad timings.

Priced way over the market rate for a coffeshop stall. Nothing outstanding about the food. Too expensive n yet stingy on the food ingredients. Order the special w extra ingredients but they gave the $4 cheaper version, had i not realised n asked, i'll definitely but short changed. Ramen soup had almost all been absorded by the noodles even before comsuming onsite. Noodle n soup has a bitter taste to it. Definitely NOT recommended to patronise. Better off w other better n value for money foodies at other stall in the same coffeshop.
My first 1 star review as imo, seriously this stall need a major revamp on its pricing/food quality.
Second time here - food is amazing, large portion and cheap. Seating at coffee shop is also easily available and clean.

When I was queuing to buy prata , the lady told me to wait and she took about 5 minutes to settle her stuff and when I told her I wanted prata she rudely said that she already told me that there is no prata as the cooks were on a break but clearly she did not tell me that. Furthermore , she spoke rudely and was very impatient. Horrible experience

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Food is good as always. Must pick thai sausage, fake abalone slice, and seaweed for the soup. Would be so much better and comfortable if the cleanliness can be done better. Will still come back again for the food.

Food - 3.8/5
Waiting time - 1/5
Service - 1/5

Food:
More affordable than putien restaurant. Taste decent, like any good standard zhi char stall, but wont say extraordinary. Menu was comprehensive.

Waiting time:
Dabaoed food for Sunday dinner. Placed order at 6.10pm, which i thought was pretty early. But only received the food at 7.10pm and after atleast 5 times of asking to check on my order.

Service:
Understandable that shop is crowded and everyone was busy. But when i keep asking the helpers to check on my order, they always ask the main guy directing the flow, and in the end no reply was given. Went directly to the main guy to ask to check, he didn't even look at the orders he had in hand and told me to come back 15min, and say its cooking already. Went back 10min later to check again, and asked if the dishes even started cooking. And he finally went to take a look and hurried his chefs on my order. Just felt he should be honest about the situation. If the dishes were not cooked, just be truthful. At least we can better estimate our own waiting time and not be a fool standing there and waiting. Also they seem to have another order line which people call in and ordered, and paid when they come to collect. Those orders and those eat in orders seemed to be prioritied compared us who took the effort to walk in and order, and even paid upfront. Really upset about this whole situation.

Those who intend to try the stall can perhaps catch them at the off peak hours, or try calling in to see if u can pre order. All the best.
Food quality is good only problem is shortage of staff and food serving is small.
Very good Zi char, good cooking, dishes quite typical. Excellent fishhead steamboat
Nice Nasi Lemak that goes well with the fiery-kick XO sambal. The ayam masak merah is good add-on to complete my breakfast üôÇ

I hardly give 1 star reviews but this place deserves zero ‚Äî if there was such a rating.

Mediocre food with poor service and presentation. We ordered fish head noodle soup, hotplate beancurd, ngoh hiang, gong bao frog and curry fish head. The fish head noodle soup was tasteless unlike what was shown on the menu. The hotplate beancurd had the worst presentation by far! The curry fish head and ngoh hiang weren't too bad.

Service was horrible because I brought my grandma, but I think they just weren't welcoming or lacked situational awareness that they couldn't bother opening the doors for me to wheel her in. The waiter was also engrossed in his mobile phone game instead of giving food recommendations, and just left us halfway to "let us sort out our thoughts".

With such lackadaisical attitudes and lackluster food, I won't recommend anyone to patronize this place even if you're staying at the nearby housing blocks.
The meat and soup quality is below average. Meat is very rough. With this price, you‚Äôd be better off with Takagi Ramen, cheaper and taste better also

Overall quite good.  Just chicken a bit tasteless (although v tender) if eat without the chilli sauce.
V crowded .

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
I don't have much choices in Singapore to compare with but I think the taste is good and the price is reasonable. Its a more friendly budget version of YumCha. The food that I ordered here cost around $26.90 for 2 person. I am happy with that as my brunch. =)
Probably due to Covid-19, the space its kinda limited and of coz it's food court place so don't expect it to be comfortable and airconditioned environment but it's rather cozy and windy..

Tried the western food. But will return to try Nepalese food.
Throwback into the 70s. Friendly staff.

Good prices for set lunch on a Sunday. German beer $20 for a bucket of 4.
Oysters available as well.

Female staff forgot to place order with kitchen, wasted 30mins waiting. Also busy on handphone all the time. Kitchen staff also didnt expedite order and unapologetic.
Fortunately food was good, otherwise a total disaster...

1 particular staff gave really bad service. Saw a few tables of customers were uncomfortable with the services too.

Advise first timers to read the comments before heading down, to get a sense of the type of service you will be getting.
Good very yummy, a lot of varieties

It is cheap and its good. You are buying what its worth!

Pricing will equate the taste of the food. Actually, even better!

If i would want to eat prata in the neighborhood, this is the place to go.

Staff are friendly. Location is very accessible.

I wish though that the store will be tidier. Thus the rating is 4. It could be 5 if clean and organized.
Mentai Mayo Fries deserved a zero star. Do not order this unless you top up at least 2 pack more of Mentai. Almost like regular French Fries.

Run by 2 young guys, wasn‚Äôt crowded on a Sunday afternoon. We ordered the Prime black pepper steak ü•© medium well. It‚Äôs was a good cut of meat, cooked to the degree I wanted‚Ä¶ yumz!! Black pepper sauce was pretty good. It‚Äôs comes with 2 side dishes. Overall value for money, $11 per plate and I enjoyed the steak. Easily accessible by private transport and the multi storey carpark is just beside the coffeeshop so no worries about getting caught in the rain.
Always love the sashimi salad! I think it's the best among the Japanese eating outlets.

The restaurant is clean.
The staff is able to answer the question.
The food is presentable and nice.
One of my favourite eatery to order from Grab. Love their soup based Mala.
Tables are limited and luckily, I went there after lunch and managed to have a seat. Nice selection of food to choose from. Enjoyed my late lunch.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: The portion given that day was quite generous, beef rendang and stingray were the two making its way to my favorite list.

Tabaoed this for dinner on our way to our friend‚Äôs house nearby. Ordered the Nepalese chicken with rice and 2 different types of salmon. Price isn‚Äôt the cheapest but food is good enough. Like the chicken very much due to its seasoning. Rice, vegetables and mashed potatoes are all good too. Service is as good as what I remembered it to be. The teriyaki salmon can be softer though. Otherwise all good.

1st time try out the food is tasty & value of money. A few dishes are recommended like sambal Kang kong, sweet & sour pork, beancurd with pork & preserved vegetable, Herbal chicken, Yam Ring  & golden cereal prawn. With definitely come back to try other dishes.

Amazing BBQ food! Reasonably priced and really tasty.

Ordered a platter combo ($25) that came with 2 sides.

Definitely worth dropping by.
Great food and friendly staffs. Will come again. The chili is homemade and awesome!

I ordered 2 veggie burritos for takeaway today - 1 was alright but unfortunately the other was a soggy, deconstructed mess. The filling was falling out as I was unwrapping the burrito and the tortilla wrap was soggy, broken and very unpleasant to eat.

Rating 2 stars for inconsistency.

I personally love this Japanese restaurant very much, and usually go there for dinner over once a month. The food is fresh and tasty, the atmosphere is relaxing too. The price is roughly 25-40 SGD per person.
Taste good
good food, good wine, good environment, good boss but not the Philippino stuff, rude and no common sense to clear the table for us

This place straight up scams people. Prices vary every time I visit and the people running this place gives different excuses for the change in price. The food is terrible and salty, especially their curry. Avoid this place at all cost.

Today i bougth 2 pkt chicken frm jurong west st 91 its was so saltish tat we cannot even eat it.
End we throw the both pkts.
Plssss taste before serving customer in future.
We are not get it fr free.
$9 is also a hard money fr us.
Plsssss take note ya.
Underrated place with extremely legit and affordable Sichuan food. ÁÉ§È±º and Ëæ£Â≠êÈ∏° are must-trys!

Was in this area and dropped by here for lunch. Similar concept to a competitor outlet at rail mall, this is a much better offering. Perhaps it‚Äôs due to the weekday lunch hour, it wasn‚Äôt crowded. And we were well served by the staff. We waited a while for the food to be prepared.

The egg prata is doughy, not the crispy type. I love the curry though. Both served hot and fresh.

Just as fresh and hot is the Briyani. Even the fish is hot. I like the fluffy rice.

The coffee is not to my taste, but it‚Äôs decent enough. Nice clean environment. Couldn‚Äôt find the toilet tho. There‚Äôs a wash basin. Price wise perhaps a tad cheaper than the rail mall competitor.

Fans of Indian fare who want gd decent food in upp Thomson road area can consider checking this place out.

A small little place but has great service. The wait staff on duty was polite and friendly. She was patient in answering my queries about the food and assisted me in filling in the form to order the food.

The food was served fast. The Buta Yaki Don was flavorful and the mekajiri sashimi was fresh. Although there were only three slices of sashimi, it is worthwhile to note that the slices are quite thick.

Price is reasonable for the quantity and quality of the food.

A nice touch was that the wait staff bothered to check with the customers on their opinion of theme food and service during payment.
This place took 30 minutes to serve a plate of Gyoza. I don‚Äôt even need that long to make it from scratch.

An east-meets-west fusion restaurant at the Maxwell Chambers Suites.
The food looks simple but it is unique and delicious. Every private dining room is directly accessible from the passageway outside.
There is ample parking behind the building, though a little dark and quiet at night.

Don't buy the 5-star reviews you see here. This restaurant is absolute trash -  as I'm sure you can see from the countless other 1/2-star posts. Food portion is not worth it for the price of the meal when you can get something of higher quality and quantity from Pasta Express nearby. Heck it, I think even the food courts are better. Although I have to say the 1-star mainly comes from the extremely rude Chinese uncle who prepares the food here. Has absolutely no patience with customers and speaks rudely.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Food is great.
Love the si-chuan cold noodle with chicken. Really delicious & my family enjoyed it.
Fried rice was average.
Oh yes.. and XLB was nice.
Horrendous service

Came to have dinner today. Didn‚Äôt get the duck but the other dishes like the lobster mapo tofu, and the fish maw soup were delicious. Chun Hong was serving us and was very attentive and cheery.

Thanks for the wonderful dinner.

We were a party of 3 and ordered 6 items with the intention to sample as much as we can. The pricing was very reasonable and perhaps the food was just about as well. Starting with the least - KL fried hokkien mee was very disappointing (texture of noodle was so limp), also not impressed with the claypot rice which lacked flavor (it needed quite a bit of dark soy sauce to salvage), garlic chicken was OK (its nice having fresh chicken with all the chopped up/ odd bits). But we certainly enjoyed the ‰∏âÊ•ºÁ±≥Á≤â, Âí∏ËõãÊéíÈ™® and the spinach in 3 eggs. Will try new dishes (maybe curry fish head) if we do return.

Very delicious and simple teochew cuisine ! Prices are cheap and good ! A must try is their signature teochew mixed soup with fish egg ü§§Been coming here quite frequently for it üòébut do call in advance to check if there is stock for fish egg.

Great service, observant and meticulous. They took note and very careful with our special dietary order.

Great food with affordable price, generous portion too.

Classy ambience however noise from kitchen is a bit loud.

Vegetarian friendly.
A quiet corner serving decent food. I enjoy the cool breeze and tasty prata that should be eaten promptly before turning cold and hard, albeit retaining good flavour.
Ordered from foodpanda and was blown away by the good taste and generous portion. Came in 25 mins...very fast. Will order again.

Horrendous dining experience, do not order their drinks, Teh O ice super black and tasteless with no sugar. Their putien noodle has no taste and very little to no meat. Worst restaurant! Don't waste ur time and money here
Foods were good. Service was good too. Love the spicy clam dish.

This restaurant is at 25% discount takeaway for Saturday and Sunday.
What can I say? I keep come back after first try.

Pekkin duck
Roast pork
Dim sum
... I m going again
The Nasi Lemak is cheap and good. Long queue. So come early to beat the queue.
Good food. Good price for a mall setting.

Had Barramundi with Otah & curry sauce under national dy promotion. Fish is fresh and juicy but pity the otah wasnt much thinner then in menu. It comes in set meal if you are willing to top up $6.80 to get a soup and dessert.

We got half a duck, a mixed platter of char siew and roast pork and individual bowls of noodles. The food, including the noodles, was pretty salty. Apart from the duck, the rest of the food came in small portions. This is especially so for the noodles, which cost $2 each. The char siew was the saving grace of the meal though. The noodles also came with lots of lard pieces.

Service was also quick.
Excellent Herbal Angelic duck, assam fish, baked cod fish fish maw soup. Good service. pricey though

Not good. Not bad. Just very average. Definitely overpriced for what it is.

Two things entertained me about this place:

1) We overheard a young girl telling her father ‚ÄúThis food is disgusting‚Äù - that cracked me up. Her father and I exchanged a chuckle.
2) The restaurant is for some reason using a large amount of space, right next to where the customers are sitting, to store boxes. It just looks funny! Attached a picture to illustrate.
If you are the someone who misses Malaysian delicasies, Anson Town can satisfy your gourmet cravings especially the cheong fun serve in curry gravy

Their offers are pretty good.
Love their potato with sour cream, chives and bacon bits. Pro tip, you can ask for seconds.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: have been to three of their outlets, I prefer this outlet more as the environment is more spacious, feel less claustrophobic. food is good and affordable. well ventilated!

Good food value prices. The steam fish was fresh and tasty. Grill squid is out of this world good. (To note, it doesn‚Äôt taste as good when you tarpow). And the tom yum soup packs a punch too.

Nice hardworking and friendly couple. Please support.
Nice place where you can find Filipino cuisine. Nice retrace for afternoons and evenings

Not the usual heartland western food. Serves (entry/mid level) restaurant quality meats and seafood (western style) for lower than restaurant prices. Heartland ambience. Definitely recommend the lobster and beef steak combo and the bottled Belgian white beer bucket.

Excellent service from Chunyan at Paradise Hotpot! She really went out of her way to rectify a mistake by the foodpanda rider.

We ordered the 2 pax set via foodpanda, and order came with only the ingredients without the soup base. When we called the restaurant, the staff was already waiting for my call, and explained that the rider had picked up the ingredients and left without collecting the soup base. She then got my address and cabbed down to my place herself to deliver the missing soup base. Very grateful for the excellent service and great attitude.

If there were 6 stars we would give 7 üòÑ

The place is convenient located at street level. There is a big open carpark which is only about 100m away. They served dim sum lunch. The place is not very big so need prior reservation to avoid disappointment. There are various types of dim sum for selection and also some ala carte dishes. The seafood crispy noodles and the clay pot tofu with scallops were very good. The char siu with roast duck were done very well. The har gao, siew mai, xiao long bao and the rest were equally great.
Great atmosphere, food and staff. Been here a couple of times and always a good experience.

First time trying. Only 2 staffs serving and cashier but they were quite efficient.  We ordered the $12.9 seabass steam with clear tomyum, curious how would it be with the price.  It was big, fresh and tasty. 4 thumbs up. We also ordered $6 chicken basil fried rice (big portion and yummy) and $6 fried kailan with crispy pork (somehow they served us just fried kailan without pork but we decided to accept,  it's a bit salty but ok). Will come back to try other dishes
Very spicy

This hainanese western food is something close to my hearts. Had it since early 90s and the shop probably shifted a few times but within the same area. If you like affordable western food, this is good.
Very good indian restaurant  . Run by friendly  people. Certain items Might be just a little bit pricey but very good food and atmosphere.

A 5-star for the very affordable food available. They could have charged more but due to their "give back to community", their prices are pegged to the community around them - many elderly who are happy to pay for the small amount of sustenance that they rquire for the day on a day to day basis. The simple $1, YES! ONE SG DOLLAR, nasi lemak with ikan bilis not only fills the stomach but also the heart of the community.
Their services are good & courteous. Sometimes long line of customers and orders in bags. Charges are really affordable.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Had the naan and the black pepper mutton. Enjoyed the food a lot, good naan and spicy tender mutton!

Had a family dinner here to celebrate the start of Q3 and Q4. Ordered sashimis, agemono, sushi (salmon and tuna) based on the wait staff's recommendations. Food were fresh, really delish and service is good. Ambient is also very apt for a nice chill family time. What stood out? The yellowtail collar, stingray fin, house sushi, wagyu don, and kurobota pork. Really had a great time. Feel relaxed and ready for the work week again.
Come in 45mins  to 60 mins prior to your meal time. Order taking at counter slow, order peeping  is extremely slow as well.

Update: standards seem to have declined due to a change in management. The phad thai was sorely lacking in intense wok hei flavours and wasn't as moist as before. Even the addition of sugar and spice could not save the dish.

One of the better Thai food stores at Toa Payoh Central. Dishes are priced competitively, portions are sufficient and food quality is consistent with the multiple patronage.

The stall owners are also receptive to customers' requests. Favourite dishes include the plethora of fried rices (particularly the pineapple fried rice), phad thai (which they cook extremely well, it wasn't too dry, sufficiently moist and packed with ingredients) and their mango salad. Cashless payment is accepted here.

Din Tai Fung was an all time favourite for me for many years but this visit was a disappointment. The service is good as always but waiting time to get a table is still long.

The disappointment is with the xiao long bao and spicy dumplings. The xlb is not longer as flavoursome. The spicy dumplings are sticky together and tough where meat tastes like a flour dough more than pork. I used to love this dish and can have 2 bowls but now it is neither spicy nor sour.

On the lucky end, the fried rice with shrimps and chicken soup are still as good.

But as always and recently, everything is getting  pricey. For the price it is, it is not quite worth it.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Service was average, did not clear the empty plates while they serve new dishes and when crew sees glass empty they did not take initiative to ask and refill. Need to prompt them, then they will clear for us and refill. The Yu-Sheng presentation was one of the worse. Totally no green as u see from the photo. Taste was okay though. Dim sum did not match the price, nothing unique about it.

To be honest the broth does not taste authentic. It has this bitter taste and not refreshing or tasty.

But what surprised me is the teriyaki chicken ($5) is pretty good. The gyoza ($6) has this thick skin covering the meat inside. Worth a try too.
You can get most of the local hawker foods reasonable price. Due to covid, only 2 pax per table, so there is waiting time . Waiting time per order and table est 20mins.

Maybe there is a stand in kitchen crew.  The food is a far cry from the Vivo branch.   Even the way the food is prep seems different- our chicken / pork seems to be prep in advance and then reheated via pan fried or microwaved.  And there‚Äôs hardly sauce on top although it tasted salty.  Will not be coming again even if we are now living nearer to Jem than Vivo.

One word of caution for the owner- with an open space open-open dine-in your staff do need to watch out for patrons to ensure no free riders who eat and go without paying üòä

Wonderful staff! Food is delicious !
Especially the crab! Good deal!
Recommended ‚ù§Ô∏è

5 stars for the yummy food and the value for money
1 star for the very very very long wait.
Went at off peak timing at 5pm. Place was relatively empty but due to numerous super huge delivery order, had to wait almost 25 to 30 min for food

So average out to a 3 stars here.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
The staff there were very kind and helpful, especially Jov! She was super friendly and made our experience there great. She's the kind of staff that would help secure loyal customers to your restaurant. Hope she gets rewarded accordingly :)

The food here is really q good for the price you're paying, definitely worth a try if you're around the area
I wish i could give 0 star rating. Screwed up service to max. Either u will recive ur order late, wrong order, or never at all..... they can happliy cancel ur order 45 min later after accepting...

It's good that they are starting to get more footfall in this quiet food court. They have also expanded into a central kitchen that houses various brands like king of fried rice & Texas chicken. Will also recommend the Korean don at gogiyo. Their teriyaki salmon don is really fresh and the serving is huge!

Huge variety of Malaysian cuisine, don‚Äôt go too near to closing time, most of the time, they will not entertain your orders by saying they are closing soon. Some might be rude to you, but this is 100% authentic Malaysian experience!

First and last time to be here! We order sashimi, beef ramen, chicken ramen, and abalone
The good thing was the salmon and eggs only, the rest was terrible! Cost me $60 incld tax and service charge. The soup was bland, overall not the taste i was hoping to be at-least-good enough. I rather go L2 to eat china beef noodle, than this one. Very disappointed
Food so so. Price is reasonable.

After watching the review of a food vlogger we decided to try.

They go by weight and it's not the cheapest.  If you want to really get your money's worth, just take all meat, seafood and mushroom. Forget anything green.

None of the food is labelled so, choosing the meat is just a matter of fatty or lean.

They are very responsive on the telegram chat so just check with them for any queries.

Ideally, start your meal no later than 6.30 pm.  The queue gets out of control towards the night. We stepped in at 6pm and we were eating in less than 15 minutes.

The spice level of "low" is equal to "Wei la" outside.

The fried potato, is no different from potato chips, nothing really amazing, maybe potato chips are cheaper.

The fried lotus root was interesting. Since we do not find the fried lotus root chips outside easily, it is worth a return trip. Our nitpick is, they just fry the items without seasoning, no Cajun powder no salt n pepper. (OK maybe the dory had salt)  perhaps my expectation were shaped by LokLok and therefore too high.

I would really have preferred if they deep fried then somehow integrated the mala sauce with the fried items, maybe offer a dip. Maybe I am too influenced by loklok.

The scrambled eggs are just scrambled eggs without any seasoning.

Every other item was typical of a Mala shop. Either you agree with the taste or disagree. I agree with the taste.

The green and brown drink is Thai milk tea. The green one seems to be Thai milk tea with jasmine green tea. They are not really strong brew, but worth the $2.50 price tag. Probably one of the cheapest Thai milk tea.

There is a strange smell on the tray, but small matter, just put it away.

Unlike many other eating places in NTU there is no student price for flashing your student card here.

This place is not worth a detour. It is worth trying if you are in the area or you drive.
The clay pot crab bee Hoon soup is not that great.

Nice western foods, the line is long and so does the wait. We had porkchops $6.50, portion is big for two persons, meat is tender and juicy, french fries are crispy and coleslaw is nice too. Will be back to try others.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content:
One bowl a day to supplement original Qi, Strengthen body and  debate fatigue.  I will usually drink it in the morning (or anytime before 4pm) simply by thawing a pack and double boiling it or microwaving it. Fast and convenient!

The best part is that each bowl is made from halal chicken and has a is very pleasant taste with no bitter aftertaste, just like drinking homemade chicken soup.
Don't believe the 5 stars review!

Queue is long. I ordered the mee soto. Though it‚Äôs soup but it taste more like mee rebus w the peanut sauce taste. Not my kind of thing.

The black chilli n the bergadil is alright only

Maybe the mee rebus n the satay is better though I didn‚Äôt order. Lots of others do

Ordered a sirloin steak. Nicely done. Baked potatoes was nicely done not overly dry - which happen the last time i was here - moist and tender to soak in the sour cream, bacon bits and spring onions (miss the chives).

Ordered a rare steak which they served as per my order. Just the way i like it.

Was very well satisfied with my dinner tonight.
Superb, highly recommended ,for Halal Japanese cuisine
The food was indeed good as what I had in Shanghai. Waited for 30min. but it‚Äôs ok as no need to queue up outside, they will call back.

Extremely bad experience. How is it possible that a chicken rice restaurant have no chicken to sell especially on Mother's Day? Extremely bad planning! It's a day of celebration, and you should anticipate that it's a day where crowds will gather especially since covid restrictions have been eased! Extremely disappointed as this is not the first time I have exprienced this. Will not recommend this place.

Went on a Friday night around 7pm and there are 1-2 seats left. Service was okay. You can order your food via QR code.

Ordered the pan fried buns, minced meat noodle and pork fillet. Pan fried buns were good though the base of the crust is rather on the thicker side. Noodle was okay nothing amazing. Pork fillet was pretty oily and didn't have much taste.

Will probably return for the pan fried buns.

Friendly staffs and comfortable place to dine in.
First time eating ponni rice and the taste is really different from those Thai rice.
The mutton masala set was delicious, love the gravy üòã.
The paneer in tomatoüëå.
Tandoori chicken briyani was ok....for me the briyani rice was a bit overpowered by spices. Tried the masala tea, it was good but a bit sweet.( forgot to ask for less sugar).
The fish head curry was a disappointment though. I've had better at other eatery

Pros: Noodle texture springy. Fishballs are bouncy and tasty üòã. Pork lard is the best I‚Äôve tried in a noodle dish, not hard and dry.
Cons: I think the Tow Pok, Chilli and Seaweed is out of place. It felt like having a combination of JB wanton Mee + Teochew Fishball noodle + YTF + KL chilli ban mian.
Overall: A good bowl of Malaysia Noodle. Just not the typical fishball noodle.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Would rate 9/10 for the nasi lemak sold! Would have rated 10/10 if not for the pricing! It's a little too expensive but overall, the nasi lemak is delicious. Definitely it's a must to try! They have few other shops too!
Nice ambience to have dinner and some drinks after to catch up with friends
My favourite hotpot place. The lunchtime discount is awesome. Can‚Äôt wait to go back again.
Prata gravy is special and nice. Fried Maggie not bad too. Beverages like teh tarik & kopi tarik is good too.
Avoid ordering from them at all cost. The delivery time just keeps on delaying.

Each bowl of Lor Mee comes with braised egg, pork slice, Kang Kong and fish cakes. Thick starchy and flavoursome broth is ladled onto springy yellow noodles. With their homemade chilli sauce and vinegar, the Lor Mee tastes as good as it looks, makes you want to go back for more.

Prawn Mee was equally delicious as well. Soup had distinct a rich flavour and pleasant aroma. Every sip of the soup, will open up your appetite more and I just couldn‚Äôt stop indulging. Definitely a great choice for a quick and delicious brunch.
Nice old school western food

Staff on shift was genuine n kind, very dedicated to her job and was nice to share her experience and changes in jobs toswrve others n finds joy in her everyday life which keeps her going. Loved the outcome fluffy, kueh and yet crisp thick pandan waffle that tasted nice even plain, although on pricey end of $2.30 for plain but alls worth the trip down cuz i loved the auntie that served me tday(:

Went during lunch and so you get either a selected drink/side/dessert with any main. The size of the portions actually differ from outlet to outlet. The portion here is actually good for me but when I dined at the Balestier outlet, it was a very generous portion with a mountain of pasta and salad that it was enough for 2, but that outlet has since closed.

Service crew is helpful and polite and food was served relatively quickly from time of ordering that I actually suspect if they had already pre-cooked everything and just microwaved it to serve.

Payment was slow, queued almost 10 minutes just to pay and that is a long time to stand considering that there were only 2 other person in front of me.
This stall has not changed after so many years. The price is still reasonable and portions are huge! Every time I am in the area, this is my top option!
cheap n nice foods

Ordered the saba fish don and it comes with complementary salad and miso soup.

Fish is a lil too light in terms of flavor. Could‚Äôve been crispier on the skin and marinated more.

I missed Penang prawn mee. Chance upon this stall behind a so-called back alley at Toa Payoh central just next to the bus interchange.

The prawny flavour is just not there. Well at least not enough. It comes with two medium sized prawns, half an egg, pieces of pork slices.

But for $5 it was a pretty big bowl. Hope they will improve the prawn mee soup flavour.
I have been calling for a few days to make a reservation for 10 persons but no one picks up the phone.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Really awesome Teochew food but not the easiest place to get to by public transport. You probably need to drive there but it's worth it. Atmosphere is good and food is even better, especially their braised duck
Rude and slow cashier, buck up on service

The food is fresh and taste good. Environment is clean and tidy. The table setting makes me feel a little congested where I could easily hit the people sitting behind me. The price is a little high given the type of food they provide. Overall a good experience.
had chicken chop with pasta. overall taste not bad, gd portion too. price was $8.50 er which i felt slightly ex cos dis was a stall in non-aircon coffeeshop.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: The prata is cooked only on 1 side. The curries are good just the prata is white as snow on 1 side is already minus points

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: The food is alright but during lunch and dinner time you may expect to wait very long . If you intend to eat their pomfret steamboat you need to wait at least 30 to 45 min just for them to thaw the fish.Service so so don‚Äôt expect too much

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Nice FD. Crispy hot prata. The other one on same level not nice.

Update covid phase 2 tight:

All food available here. Gd job alfatthah.

I go prata shop at Sembawang Rd there, can tell me mee goreng don't have.

Alfatthah my supper place! Yishun people all come support

I stumbled unto this joint while walking past. Price was reasonable considering that the rib eye was quite substantial. It didn‚Äôt taste very different from the others modern style no frills western food stalls like Aston‚Äôs, chargrill etc. Doneness was quite uneven though.
Nice view n service is great!

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Amazingly delicious Indian styled grilled chicken and yummy chicken biriyani. Looking forward to visit the restaurant once the lockdown measures are lifted.

Heard that the Chef David is going to be posted out. I will be very upset and will not visit Yuba Hut in Poiz. Love the way he prepares the food for us. Please do not transfer him out. As we supported since day 1. Tks

Went with my family just before the lockdown and tried their chicken and mutton briyani, and chicken murtabak. Best I ever tried!

The mutton was so tender that it kinds of "melt in the mouth". The flavour of the rice was made just right (does not have that overwhelming spice taste). When the mutton, rice and gravy were eaten together, it gave a homely and familar feeling which is satisfying.

The chicken briyani was good as well. The chicken meat was tender and not dry.

The chicken murtabak had a special taste. It was slightly cripsy on the outside and had a slight lingering sweet taste. I like it!

It was an air-conditioned and nice place. The kitchen was properly separated from the dining area so my clothes didn't have that food smell or feel after the meal.

The individual serving size was adequate and will satisfy the general population.

Would really like to try how their pratas as well if I had more stomach capacity but will definitely visit them again (when the situation allows it)!

Very nice quiet place to drop by on weekdays . I believe this used to be the Xin Hua Lou in some Food courts which serves putien lor mee at a much cheaper price than PuTien.

The $8.90 bowl of lor mee was generously filled to the brim with lots of ingredients , we were really surprised it came with a 20% discount too on weekdays . In a period where prices are rising and everyone just jump on the bandwagon to take a cut , it‚Äôs heartening to see some eateries still doing their part to maintain fair pricing .

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Food is tasty, price is reasonable (range from $4). I like the Tom Yam soup ($5), pineapple fried rice ($4). Patthai ($4)is good, a little on the sweet side. Authentic Thai food at hawker price. Definitely going back for more.
Tasty juicy tender yakitori. Price below $10 comes with tea. Have to wait 15-20mins during peak hours but you can be sure every bowl is prepared with much TLC

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: super good & affordable, fast service too.. very convenient venue as well, always return üòÅüòÅ

There were in total at least 8 dishes including the dessert (Mango sago)
The food was tasty, though abit inclined towards salty side. Overall the food is delicious üòãüòãüòã

An authentic Thai restaurant: üáπüá≠
- Thai servers: checked
- Thai songs in the background: checked
- Photo of the old Thai King on the wall: checked

I ordered their Pad Thai ($6.50) and it was flavourful - the serving was generous. I did a walk in slightly before 12 on a weekday but the place was soon fully occupied with the lunch crowds.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Been a while since we had usual gathering there till yesterday for the party of 10 Koreans who has abt 10yrs average life in Singapore.
Unlike previous experiences, there are big disappointments to all of us .
- service is really sluggish. Had to press buttons multiple times to get someone come to check.
- food is in general too salty. We asked less salty after tasting first two dishes, but it didn't work despite over 10 dishes we tried.
- Manager is seems having no customer caring attitude. She even turned back although we didn't finish our requests/orders.

We spent over $1.1K including the service charge of over $100 for this type of service and food.
All really got disappointed.

Food is really delicious. The fish soup bee hoon has thick generous slices of fish. The coffee pork ribs is very meaty and soft. The prawn paste chicken wing are very Ccrispy, juicy and tender. Great place for meals with family and friends.

Tried the Thai Claypot Hotpot (jim jum). Not a lot of places in Singapore has this jim jum. $28 per set, more than enough for 2 person. The ingredients should be similar to the Mookata. The jim jum soup is good. The dipping sauce (nam jim jaew) is very nice and match very well with the jim jum. Value for the money. Good to eat especially during cold weather.

New ramen shop, an additional option especially for the Malay friends, cos it‚Äôs Halal certified. Clean, nice setting. Taste of Ramen is flavourful, though it‚Äôs a bit salty for the regular. One can opt for the clear option if you prefer something more bland. Tasty in general, though the onsen egg is a bit overcooked and being halal, it‚Äôs chicken instead of pork.

Price is reasonable and a place I‚Äôll come again, with my Malay friends along.
Awesome Nasi Lemak and Nasi Padang!

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: nice restaurant
Food quality is mediocre. Quantity is very little too. Won‚Äôt be eating from them again.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: We were served pretty quickly despite the place being crowded. The food variety is ok. Lotsa meat and my children love the garlic chicken. We ordered at least 20 plates of meats, Vegs and instant noodle for 4 of us and the bill came to only $38. We were very full by then. Will definitely go back again.

Food is decent, especially the ones from the menu. The main attraction of this place is the heathy salad bowls - however, they have reduced the options and items to be included in the body's since the time it was first introduced.
My advice for dim sum patrons. This is certainly not Express, instead the waiting time is damn long. Try it if you have spare time to wait.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Such a nice restaurent that we went to eating..they said they can make veg jain food..finally came with onion and..our happy outing end up with a family fighting.request to them please do not commit if you can not make it.thank you.
First time I came here the staff  no so happy when I asking him  the price bor the food but I still try to eat  don't had a happy mood.
The lobster bee Hoon is very good, must try. Charcoal bean curd also unique and worths try

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Nice place having lunch with business partner.

Good sashimi, below average tempura, nice beef. Service is extremely slow. Even when the restaurant has 2 tables seated, it took them 40min to prepare a set meal after repeated checks. Do not visit unless you have time to kill.

Environment is okay, next to market.
Dim sum not freshly made, taste is average.

Porridge taste good, prices are reasonable.

No services charge.
Will come again for the porridge.

ig: @_bluebulb

Food standard has drop drastically, it‚Äôs about 20-30% of their usual standard. Bluefin grilled jaw was not fresh, beef was subpar chewy for price paid, miserable small piece, taste like rejected beef from supplier. Yakisoba which is suppose to be a easy cook was mushy and tasteless.

Always like going to this restaurant but today was a real disappointment.

However service staff was attentive, that was the only saving grace.

The food came quickly and the quality of food was satisfactory. Service was extraordinary,  staff were attentive. Staff Suman upon seeing my pregnant wife provided a pillow to support her back. üëç Positive experience

No question ask, good Filipino food and value for the money! The owner itself is friendly and took time to greet customers and ask how's the food. However the Filipina waiter doesn't seem to be accommodating, we have to call her how many times and after asking question she will leave right away!! We understand that they are busy but just our 2 cent, they need to pay attention on basic customer service.

PS: All desserts are not available when we visited.
Good food. We had fisi head curry set, very tasty
The steamboat is really nice. The soup is a bit salty. Portions are reasonable. We ordered a few more dishes.
Price is reasonable and the food is also not bad. There is also promotion for duck meats per plate at only $8.80. (U.P $18).
Went to LJS NTU at 7:30 and after ordering, the cashier informed us that some of the things we ordered were sold out and they offered to give us some freebies to make up for it. Thanks abang!
Been a long time customer. Need to improve the mee goreng. Standards have dropped drastically. Giving 4 stars because I hope there will improvements
Been here twice. So far all dishes we've tried seem to be quite spot on. Kudos, keep it up.

Dining ambience is satisfactory and food is so so compared to other Jack's Place outlet.

The reason I gave it a one star review is the service level, questions unanswered by a young female wait staff.

Hope to see some improvement on service level.

Thank you

Portion is big, food is nice.

Value for money

Recently visit and I must say if you want authentic Thai food to satisfy Thai food craving, here is the place! I highly recommend here and I love their quality dishes are all at affordable price plus the staffs are very friendly.

What I have,

Soi Aroy Signature Mixed Platter.
Comes with Moo Ping (pork skewers), Lemongrass Chicken and Grilled Pork Cheeks that are marinated for 24 hours. Once served the staff will torch the pork cheek on the spot to give that smokiness and melt in mouth goodness once you bite on while the lemongrass chicken and mooping are grilled to tender perfection.

Crispy Papaya Salad with deep fried soft shell crab!! This dish was probably the most unique out of all the dishes tried. A unique rendition of the familiar papaya salad that been battered and deep fried till crispy and atop deep fried soft shell crab. Have it together with the tangy and nutty dipping sauce, I'm in heaven.

Crispy Omelette With Crab Meat.
This is another of the stand-out dishes to me.
The fried egg is not only airy and fluffy, but very crispy and not being in any way greasy as well. The added crab meat atop, adds a distinct note of crustacean sweetness to the omelette and the crab meat itself is fresh.

Thai Steamed Seabass with Lime & Chilli.
Ocean fresh Seabass steamed in special lime and chilli sauce topped with SuperThai special sauce. I like you can opt for fish fillet or the entire seabass. Fresh, tender meat paired with the spicy sauce that keeps me eating non stop.

Seafood Tom Yum Soup.
It blew me away with its depth and bold flavours. Sour and spicy which goes perfectly with rice and the seafood is really fresh here.

Claypot Vermicelli with Prawns.
The prawns are fresh and succulent and the vermicelli is bursting with flavour from having absorbed the sauce. Pack a flavourful punch.

Fresh Oyster.
I'm very lucky that I went day they have fresh oyster and is so fresh when you dip with their sauce, you in ocean heaven!

Mango Sticky Rice.
Hard to give this Thai dessert amiss. I love this as it has the perfect firmness and sweetness of the Thai Mango thay went perfectly well with the perfect texture of the glutinous rice and coconut milk. This dessert is highly commendable.

Red Ruby with Coconut Icecream.
Coconut Icecream on top shaved ice, drizzled with sweet red syrup and fresh coconut milk. Topped with red rubies that gives a chewy crunch.

The Thai Iced Tea here is a must DRINK. Not too sweet yet strong enough taste of the tea aroma.

A place worth keep coming back to.

Oyster egg with 3 oysters and more corn flour than egg.

Claypot chicken rice is soya sauce rice.

Not worth the money

The decor and ambience really nice but unfortunately there was a table with 2 ladies and a man stole the show for the night . They were talking so loudly that I think the rest of the diners must be annoyed . They should have dine.in Broadway kopitiam! Hopefully when we come back we will have more considerate diners! restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Good choice for mookata due to...
Environment: Inside with aircond so won't hot and the smoke exhaust did the job. But definitely you clothes still smell smoky after that.
Food: minimum order of 10plate (exclude rice/noodles), most of the meat we order is tasty, soup refillable. Just nice for 2pax as we are small eater.
Sauce must try: go for special with add on garlic, chili, and lime juice.
Service: Fast, waiter are attentive.
Price: ~$30 for the one shown in photo (10plate+1rice). Depends what you order, range start from $1.80 (vege), $2 (Meat)~$4(special/seafood).

Extremely slow and poor service. Food was so so not worth the torture. They're not interested to do business. Came in and ordered. One other table who were there before us looked like they had been waiting a long time. Bad sign. The first item that came after around 40 min was a maki roll. The skewers came around the 1 hour mark. The last item garlic rice took soooo long to come after more than 1.5 hours. See photo. How does this pathetic small $10 garlic fried rice with no meat require 1.5 hours to cook? Cook rice from scratch also no need so long. We had to ask for it and the staff said they were already cooking. That was 30 min before it actually came. Even the lady boss could also tell we were upset. The place was rather busy that day they seemed to be hosting friends and family at least 5 tables of them. The lady boss was going around greeting people. Some of these guests are so familer w the place they were helping themselves behind the bar and walking around without mask. Some food items came out to their friends first even though they came after us. If you are not interested to host public then don't do business.
I tried the famed Pork Tomahawk and was grossly disappointed‚Ä¶.. I paid $16.90 for a piece of meat that was rather tough and tasteless. Overrated.

Their other dishes also look delicious. $6.50 is a bit high for coffeeshop standard but the quality is there. Adequate portions. Will come back and try other dishes.

The owner is very friendly and very passionate about his food.  He came  to Singapore to work as a professional when Singapore and China established a formal foreign relationship.

All the dishes served are awesome and reasonably priced. If you have been eating Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖÔºåÁîüÁÖéÂåÖÔºåÈÜâÈ∏° from other restaurant chains, I would recommend you to try this place for a different experience!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Reached at 11.30am when there's only 2 small table of people. Waited 45 mins and 6 fish soups served at 12.25pm. staffs simply ignore queries when we followed up with the order. Demand mandatory tracetogether check-in, which we did as required. Demand social distancing for family of 8. We have to rush to attend event at 1pm hence we left at 12.35pm with two pending San Lou hor fun that is not ready (even dabao not ready). Lol. Overall fish soup is yummy and good experience as mentioned above. Also seen two tables of customers left angrily as they were ignored by staff for 10mins... Try it once at Least. We just sat patiently and waited the whole time, followed up every 15 mins. They will also ask patrons to change seat or tables as they wish. Just be prepared to wait and get your table chairs shifted once awhile. We are regulars.

I'm regular here since they open but the food standard really drop, see how oily this 2 plates oyster egg, the one that selling soup noodles always never wear gloves. Their fingers always dip in the soup when they pass you the food. But all others stall remain quality and hygiene of foods.

Highly recommend to try

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: The queue is always long and that gave me the impression of 5 star food but I would give this place 3.5 stars! There are hits and misses as is the case with almost, if not every restaurant. I find the seasonings of most of their dishes spot on even if some of the dim sum did not make the cut for me. I liked their siu mai, har gow, prawn fritter (ÊòéËßíËôæ) the best. The rice noodle roll was not bad although I would prefer a thinner sheet. The taro balls would have gotten my thumbs up had the taro's texture been more "powdery" and less dense. I should not compare but I always use Crystal Jade's egg tart as benchmark for flaky Chinese egg tarts. Lo Mai Gai is a must order whenever I have dim sum and although the sticky rice was soft enough, the overall dish did not excite. The kopitiam had decent Kopi peng and Teh-C peng.

content:

Went on a Monday 9pm, there was only a few people. Ordered the fish & chips which was $7. Here are some of my thoughts.

1) The fish and chips is Battered Fish! Which is not easy to find.

2) Yes the battered was pretty good. Considering that now is H.A. and only can dabao, the fish was still warm and crispy after 15mins. I guess it's because of the dabao box that they used.

3) The tatar sauce has a slightly heavier onion taste, which was good.

4) crinkle cut fries was well seasoned and the mash potatoes goes very nicely w the dish.

The only down side is that the fish is quite thin, they give 2 pieces, but it's really more like a dory fillet cut into half. But I got no issue with it cause it's only $7 :) Will be back again for sure!  Didn't manage to take a picture and drown it down cause it smells too good ü§£

The menu has quite a bit of options - a decent number for vegetarian. The set I ordered had a starter, main course and dessert.

I chose mushroom soup (also has interesting option like samosas) , vegetarian pasta. The dessert is quite standard- choco lava cake with ice cream. It comes about 18.8 S$.

Also tried their Curry Fish Head set which comes with a very fleshy tasty full fish head (not one-sided served by some). The set makes a very satisfactory meal. The bee hoon and nasi goreng were just ok. Service staff very patient and polite. SAFRA members get 10% off. For a zichar, its really good. The sambal chilli there is flavourful! We had the sambal kangkong, very tasty. The deep fried pork cutlet was really good too. The fried seafood egg was like any other egg elsewhere, nothing special but still good. The pumpkin butter prawn didn't have much pumpkin, but the prawn was fresh.

The Soup is a little sweet, but it balanced well with the chilli. It may not be the best I've had, but there's things I really love about it. They use the Ipoh Hor fun kind of kuay Teow rather then the usual big ones, very smooth and goes well with the broth. They even peel the middle sections of the prawns, for this I gave 1 more star. I love prawn heads, and most places you will need to deshell yourself if there's head intact, or they served totally deshelled prawn. It's a lot more work to peel only the middle section, for this I'll definitely come back for more.

Chicken Steak($7.50)

The fish head curry was very thick and flavourful, but they give you half a head of fish so we felt that it was on the pricy side.
Overall not too bad.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: saw a boy drop the salmon and ruined it. the cashier immediately came and cleaned it up and wrote it off FOC. 10/10 service.

Now you m not a fan of ‚ÄúWestern‚Äù hawker stalls and have tried a few, but this place blew me away! Their fried chicken wings were delicious! The batter was nice and crispy with the flavor that outshines KFC. I wish they had spicy!!! Their steaks were nice and tender. Great deal for the price I paid! Be sure to order it rare because when it‚Äôs served on a hot plate, the steak will become medium. Also, nice touch in the mashed potatoes. They are served in the form of deep fried balls. Overall, I will definitely come here again!

Affordable, old-school taste western food. The mashed potato balls are a must have!

UPDATE (19 Sep): they have now moved to Block 168 Toa Payoh Lor 1 - Maxim Coffeeshop.
