Great 1-for-1 lunch time deal! Food was really nice and value for money, food also came quite fast. Overall, love this place ü§©

IMO absolutely the best Hor Fun in SG and beyond....soup base uses Pork Belly soup (Áå™ËÇöÊ±§0 that's been prepared ahead....resultant Hor Fun is steeped with subtle flavours and wok hei....and floating in between the Hr Fun is the pork lard ...heavnely
Remind me of the old days.

Hidden away from the main alley of Toa Payoh Central, this cafe served quite a wide range of western dishes, pasta, pizza, steak, lamb, dessert, ice cream and even beers! Tried their lamb shank, the meat is really tender and fall of the bone but it still have the gamey taste of the lamb. Thought it would have more spice mask it. The mash potatoe lack flavour and not smooth. The sweet potato fries is a bit too thin but it is crispy. The service is fast even for the lamb dish!

1st time here.
1) Rojak & bee hoon going nearly 40sgd. We didn't even ordered much. Same rojak items taken from hawker would only cost max 15sgd.
2) Ordered white bee hoon but came red been hoon. When i told counter wrong order, he blamed me which I told him i ordered right and he acknowledged. Portion so little...
3) Long waiting time. I finished my rojak then came the been hoon. Wrong bee hoon, changed...took even longer...
Just a hyped up & overrated rojak place, taste about the same as any hawker centre's. Not worth the price, but rojak is acceptable anyways. Oh well...but then.. go hawker centre more worth it la...trust me!
Wanton soup is good but the mix meat ramen is not value for money as it is just a normal dry noodle with very little meat. Not recommended to try the met ramen
Good food as usual! 3 pax around $100

Checked out this western stall that specialized in smoked meat at one of the coffeeshop of the industrial area in AMK street 62. I was there around 2pm and the lunch crowd has already died down. We order the meat platter for 2 which comes with 2 choices of sides (SGD$25), creamy pasta (SGD$5.50) and a Agilo olio (SGD$4.50).

Food didn‚Äôt take long to be served. The meat platter consisted of smoked brisket, pork belly and turkey.The sides were garlic mash and fries. Meat was average to be honest, Mash was bland, could do with more seasoning. Pasta was quite decent though, I liked the idea of having an onsen egg to go with the pasta.

Will I come all the way for this? Probably not. But in general, for the portion wise, it‚Äôs quite value for money.

Heng Hwa Fried Bee Hoon was light and clean - though I can feel that some people may think of it as tasteless. But honestly speaking, their chilli is so shiok that even if you are on 'bee hoon too is tasteless' camp, just smother some of their chilli on and you will be converted instantly. Another dish that I would highly recommend is Stir Fried Sliced Yam - the combination of light crispy batter and a drizzle of sweet sauce was too darn addictive. The Sweet and Sour Pork was also solid, can feel the slab of lean meat on each piece (i.e. not 30% meat, 40% fat, 30% batter like some places). Also, they are generous on portion and is very wallet friendly.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content:
6 of us went for a lunch on Saturday. Ordered Chicken Lolly pop and Chicken 65 for starters. Both were really nice and crispy and well flavoured.
For mains.. we ordered Naan and few choice of curries.
The bearer recommended Kongu Naattu Chicken curry and Mutton Nenju elumbu kolombu. We ordered both.. nenju elumbu kolombu was a let down.. overly spiced and the mutton bone pieces were full of koluppu ( fat).. unable to eat.
We also ordered prawn masala and that was an excellent choice to go with Naan.
Overall, taste of most items were very good.
Food served within 5 mins of order .. not seen any restaurant serving food this fast. Excellent!!
Will surely return again.

I‚Äôm reviewing the dim sum buffet that is available on weekdays 3pm-5pm. Their style is they will serve dish by dish via push carts instead of ordering yourself. And when all dishes are served, there will be a ‚Äòlast order‚Äô.

The problem came when they served the Xiao Long Bao, I told the server to give our table 4 trays, but to my surprise there are only 2 pieces per tray. But all other dim sums have 3 pieces?? Hence it‚Äôs not enough for my table so I ask another staff to get us more xlb, but she said there will be last order soon and we can order as many as we want. Ok. So during the last order, I asked for 8 trays of xlb and nothing else, 10mins later the staff came out and apologise that there are no more xlb. Erm‚Ä¶.. I‚Äôm paying for a ‚Äòbuffet‚Äô, I don‚Äôt understanding what they mean no more xlb, if no more then the chefs can make more right?
Really made me lose face since I‚Äôm the organiser, my table some eat 1 piece some eat 2 pieces only, despite being a ‚Äòbuffet‚Äô.

Most of the food was great though. Maintained the same standard as during my last visit before covid.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Ordered a truck load of food. Had to wait quite awhile to que cause of the crowd. Recommended to go early.
1st batch of Siew mai was raw, informed them and they did a quick swap. Turned out great!
Har gow had super plump prawns, super worth it.
Best dish was the steam black bean pork rib.
It's at a coffee shop, recommended to sit outside, away from the zichar stall if not you'll be perspiring like we did.
Convenient Location
V

Popular lunch place so there‚Äôs usually a queue. But you can get a table quickly if it‚Äôs just 1 or 2 pax. Ordered the daily special tomato chicken noodle and was told that there‚Äôs only the dry version (though the menu shows it with soup). Found it ok only. Star dish was the cold tofu (which my friend recommended) - nice mix of tangy and savoury flavours
Nice food!

Pass by this restaurant many times before but did not entry as it seems to be rather rustic. Recently a famous blogger visited and rave about the food here. Decided to visit since we are in the area. So glad we did! The food is simple but tasty. They serve classic Hakka food and such reasonable prices!

Waitress tonality towards answering customer questions was bad. she does answer question but her tonality would need to be improved as she somewhat seem to brush customer off.
Mdm Leong was a great host and the food was super good as always üëçüèª
Enjoyed the champion floss maki with my friends. Generous serving of floss and roe on the maki! There were a variety of dishes to choose from and staff was friendly :)

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Went to this restaurant a year ago with my family and we came out as satisfied customers. Decided to have our lunch there again today and I am retaining my 5 stars rating for them. Service wise, do not expect the kind of standard that you would find at DTF or HDL but it is generally acceptable to me considering the staff demographics. Food wise, i would say it is still pretty good, well presented, reasonable portions and good taste. The stir fried beef cubes and signature bee hoon were great.

Usually come here only to eat the Mee Rebus and Longtong. But recently I found my favourite, Clay Pot chicken rice, been ordering the $8.50 (Big) to share with my wife. More ingredients then the $5.50 (Small) ones. Worth it?

The Char Kway Teow,  not even the 2nd best off all that I've try. Told the hawker more chilli, he don't even care. Just scoop from the wok he just fried and give it to me. üëé
Will try others stalls the next time and comment, üòÑ hope I remember and not go straight to my favourite.
Horrible tasteless peanut porridge without peanut NOT WORTH

won't recommend. new place so thought to try this place. hugely disappointed with the food quality. we order the fried rice, and when it came, i asked my friend is it with cheese cause it's sticky when i tried to stir it. then i smell it and it stinks. rice already gone bad and the stench was so obvious.

signaled to this young lad which could be the boss, and he denied and said cannot be, and say their rice is ok WITHOUT even smelling it. he left the plate of rice on our table still, went to the kitchen to ask his guys, came back to take the rice, and then came back super apologetic and said the rice turn sour cause it's very hot inside. üò∂‚Äçüå´Ô∏èüò∂‚Äçüå´Ô∏èüò∂‚Äçüå´Ô∏è puzzled right???

anyway the food wasn't nice at all. the buns skin were super thick, the noodle drenched in oil.

hope the owners do something about it. the menu and photos looks promising but we left disappointed.

Pan fried local style, the chicken chop comes with brown sauce, baked beans, coleslaw, fries and a slice of garlic bread. The pork chop is also quite tender. Portions are hearty, but the taste of the chops can be better.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Long que but poor taste..  Restaurant pricing but at poor food quality...!!  Chee chong fun skin was so thick.. Fried stuff was too saltty..  Har kaw skin was too thick too !!..  It was a total disappointment... Porridge quality was acceptable.. Pricing is way too high.. Damage $75..!! .. Liu sao bun is not watery but with solid yellow hardened paste!...  Just disappointment..!!  Avoid if can!

Waffle is freshly made, nice and crunchy

Pork ribs portion is huge and the meat came off the bones easily. Chicken chop portion is small taste very average.
Taste wise ok for coffee shop price. But can't be compared to the usual Japanese Ramen shops. Conclusion: good for coffee shop standard.

(Translated by Google) My experience is that if you have it, you have it, and if you don't have it, you don't have it. Make it clear in advance üòì

It kinda ruined our marriage, even after 4 years later my husband and I still argued due to this. Couples please reconsider if you want to hold your once in a lifetime wedding in this restaurant. Here is the post 4 years ago

I host my wedding banquet on 08 Dec 18 at qianxi TPY and it was a disaster. My name was wrongly printed in the dinner menu. I didn't know dinner menu were supposed to print our name in full and no one advised.
The display TV outside is showing my wrong name as well! my guests did not know is my wedding! This is basic knowledge but yet overlooked by your management. I have emailed to your management and was simply ignored. I guess this feedback will be as well ignored!

A year later we went back to complete our meal in the same restaurant, the waitress accidentally spilled hot water onto my feet. No it wasn‚Äôt busy as we are the only table being served by one waitress at that point in time.

If anyone wish to host their wedding there think twice! new brides beware ! If you considering the same restaurant it might ruin your once in a lifetime wedding!
Chefs are very friendly, you can get some unique dishes here.

Do careful when you order your mutaba. Please be present when they cook, don't make reservation and collect when is ready.

As the prata after cook tends to be oily, I once saw the one who packet, due to oily, he gotten a cloth from the kitchen guy to tap away oil at the mutaba.

After tap dry the food, the cloth was passed back to the kitchen and the cloth was used to clean the hot plate area.

So beware.
Set meal was not worth it. Beef steak was too dry. Egg too salty. Grilled oyster mushroom too oily. Chicken thigh ok.
Loving their tempeh and lontong!

(Translated by Google) Best sambal goreng rice in yishun

(Original)
Best nasi sambal goreng in yishun
noodle and rice good and portion great
The steamed sea bream is sweet and tender. The Kai lan was also pretty good. Wouldn‚Äôt recommend the desserts here though tasted kinda weird. The red ruby was poorly executed.

Chanced upon this gem while working around this area. Had the $7 mutton briyani and $2.5 Katira drink. Finished the briyani in no time as it was delicious. Meat was not too firm and gravy was perfect for the bismati rice. Server even asked me if it was enough, should have asked for more but watching my diet lately. üòù Saw rows of the green drink and asked what it was. Thought it was avocado with gula Melaka but it‚Äôs called Katira. Not bad but not cold enough, think they just made it. The green drink tastes a bit like Bandung and the black stuff is grass jelly and some other stuff. My friend said it‚Äôs popular during Ramadan so I guess it‚Äôll be nice and cold in the evening. Place is 24 hours, think will come here with friends for supper here next time.
Yes it is nice, you can try it out by yourself. I very sure never let you down.

Ramen was cooked to perfection, and soup was nice too. Ordered the kurobuta ramen and the meat just melts in your mouth. Staff was good and friendly, definitely will be back. Do remember to give it a try!

*Too good, finished even before I took a photo haha

This is my 1st time visiting this restaurant the food was nice and great the service staff was very helpful and friendly I really like the beef hor fun and many other dishes really must give it a try will bring more friends here

I‚Äôve been to Sedap several times and the food never disappoint and is really really sedap (mouth watering); especially the chicken wings, beef rendang, otah otah, etc. Recently Sedap also serve salmon fish head curry which was surprisingly good and delicious (it has kind of more softer & jelly-like parts compared to other fish head). Definitely a must try dish for my next visit.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Tasty soup, affordable price, nice ambiance, meat are well marinated and it's flavorful... It's a nice place to connect with friends and families with sumptuous food.
Weekly breakfast place with the family. Prata is nice and crispy. Have to go early for seats
Love the chicken rendang and perkedel, will definitely come back to try other dishes.

Been eating at Uno for years. They were previously at a different location and I thought they closed down but nope, they reopened near CHIJ Toa Payoh!

Everything is delicious on their menu!

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Standard really change since they changed staff. Waited for 10 minutes for someone to serve me.

Had first visited Phoenix at the original location on a few occasions in Bukit Panjang near Phoenix LRT (hence the name?). The homely atmosphere coupled with the personal service from the owners made it a regular 'go to' restaurant. And of course the food, which is why we keep coming back.

Was happy that they moved to a location inside Science Centre, easier accessibility and quicker drive from home! They've got a bigger space now in a more cordial setting, as opposed to the 'industrial feel' location they were in earlier.

The food doesn't disappoint and spice levels were just about nice on the curries we ordered. Not too overpowering and extremely pleasant on the taste buds. Doesn't give you that heavy masala-ish feeling that makes you feel bloated and heavy. So it was very light on the spices which can pull you through a post-lunch meeting without nodding off!

Service was a tad disappointing, probably new staff that needed a bit of training? The lady owner was around and of course very friendly and hospitable as before. But service in general needed some improvement.

The new ambience is nice and a welcome change from the smaller space they had earlier. They also have an extended dining space to cater for a larger crowd, especially on weekends.

Must try item - Bhuna Gosht!
Flameless technology and its smokeless! Rest assured that you won‚Äôt smelt badly for a meal of bbq. Meat cut is good!

Went before 12pm and was able to get a table.

The Shanghaiese pan-fried buns looks, taste amazing, although I think there is just too much dough.

Same for the xiaolong baos.
Deceptively cheap cause of promo
Taste of memory, for those who visited the stall when it located at Amk S11 Beside Jubilee Sq.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Incident on 05 Feb 2022 @ around 00:20hrs at their Yishun Junction 9 outlet. Extremely bad hygiene.. Waiter cum kitchen helper took the cardboard as mat on the floor and after discarding it outside, not only did he not washed his hands, he immediately served the food to the customer even when the outlet was not crowded and the worst part was that he literally didn't even washed his hands again after cleaning his mucus, he continued to serve his customers with their food. Not even worth to patronize the outlet ever again despite I was their regular customer before.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Favorite chicken rice place in SG. Quality has lowered slightly since they sold to Jumbo and moved from their original location nearby but still good. The roast chicken, rice and sambal is still good
Nice, cosy and casual neighbourhood restaurant. Like their lamb shank and oxtail. They also have some nice Nepalese dishes.
Must try the "Porker" burger ala carte is $6 per serving a bit ex

Decent food at an appropriate price, was surprised to find out that they are opened 24 hours. Tried their fish head hot pot, braised duck (my fave from them) and others, though to be fair, the dishes were a little too salty for my taste.
Delicious
We took the Set Dinner which was offered during the Diningcity promotion ($78).   Food was very delicious and service was good!  Highly recommended!

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Food was. Love the varieties menu. Would surely come again. Normally crowded during lunches.  Parking may be a but limited unless U park 3 min away. But no regrets abt the food.
Limited seats space,  overall their foods are fairly nice, their rojak gravy is the best taste except they shld reduce the colouring

This is only the second time I've been here but the last time was at least 6 months ago. In that time, the service has become a bit lackluster and food preparation time has taken a lot longer. The food quality is still as good if not better.  Now with the market being closed for renovation, this is one of the limited options you have for Indian food.

Went there for family celebration. Food is ok, cooked decently for most dishes. Cuisine isn't much to my liking for some.

Seating is a bit congested so if you have a large group (>8 pax), expect to split up.

Mostly longish tables too so sharing food can be a bit messy or troublesome.
Their Nasi lemak never disappoints. Always seen with long queues, that‚Äôs how you‚Äôll know it‚Äôs good!!
Good food that comes with long queue. Finally found a good dry mee siam. üëçüëçüëç

Missed out my order, so I cancelled it and ordered fries instead so that they can prepare fast. No hard feelings. Then suddenly the manager Rick came to apologise to me for forgetting my order, which I wasn‚Äôt even bothered, and gave us a box of cakes! Lol so nice of him. Food is good, environment is clean. Good service
Clay pot chicken rice is good. Carrot cake was very tasty! Youtiao rojak was a little disappointing. But overall experience was still ok üëåüèª will visit to try the other food again.

Another table left early, when I pay for both table the cashier argued say the other table got 3 sauces and can even name the sauces. Already told them no sauce, once I cally mum ask them, it is no sauce, they suddenly say yaya no sauce... Trying to cheat money!!!

Giving 1 star for the soup dish @ 18.90. Supposed to be Chinese cabbage, clams and taufu soup. No Chinese cabbage at all. Ingredients are so little. DO NOT order the soup dish. Order those lor mee and fried mee Hoon is much better. Wasted trip, money and time üòû

The food seems like all precooked. Was Served right after you order. Chilli crab was the worse we've eaten, tasteless and full of starch. Pig's trotter vinegar, the meat were all dried up and there was a piece full of hair, really spoil appetite. Deep fried tilapia was OK except that for 9pax, they gave a very small fish.

Yes, very yummy fish steamboat, cold crabs and Teochew braised duck with beancurd.
We will there on 24 Feb to celebrate my birthday.

Tried black pepper lion mane and stir fry brocoli. Interesting texture for the lion mane, crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, different from the usual way of cooking lion mane. The black pepper sauce is not that prominent, can't really taste the pepper. Brocoli is fresh with some fried ginger slice and the sauce is not that salty. Service can be improved especially the staff manning the cashier counter.

Why no claypot rice? I asked after 20 minutes of waiting, twice in between 10 minutes interval, total 40 minutes, after finishing my 2 dishes ( as picture), the claypot rice haven't serve to us. After 40 minutes wait, one uncle ordered same time as us, he already finished his rice and left, while we still waiting our claypot rice, after asking twice on the order.

Bad service. Super bad service. There was no queue at all with many of seats available. I was here and orderded at 5.07pm. My claypot rice served to us at 5.50pm. And best part of the bad service? The rice was NOT fully cooked when FINALLY served to us.

I ordered cheese baked meatball pasta with mushroom. Pasta was cheesy and meatballs were tasty. The pricing is slightly more expensive than other food stalls in NTU but it‚Äôs still ok overall. Taste wise 7/10.

Ordered takeaway at Yishun Safra Springleaf. There was no visible queue when I ordered. 5 mins later, queue started to build up and I waited for another 15 mins only to find out that my order was given to another person. Without a single apology and with a nonchalant attitude, I was told by one of the staff to wait. When asked for refunds, the staff refused and started yelling with the rest in Tamil. I stood there; got my refund eventually from a Chinese looking staff who was yelled at by a staff as well.

Not sure what is happening at Springleaf. While I enjoyed the food, no one deserved such treatment. Do consider looking into this matter please? You have just lost 4 patrons permanently. *Note: I did not raised my voice or make a scene. Just want to have a decent dinner that i am willing to pay for. - not anymore.

It‚Äôs reasonably priced and they often have additional offers but that‚Äôs the best that can be said of it. Food quality is decidedly average at least for their Chirashi Don. But what can you expect really for do it all budget Japanese places? Eat here if it‚Äôs convenient for you and if you are on a budget but otherwise you‚Äôd be better off at a less budget place.
Great place for families to enjoy sushi delivered to you by cutesy robots. Quite a novel and fun experience. Go for the thick cut sashimi - no regrets!

Good range of mains with sides options. Huge servings of fries and coleslaw - but only 4 onion rings... ü§î chicken chop quite large but "monster burger" isn't really monstrous lah. Tasty enough though.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Good nasi padang place. Price reasonable. Crowded lunch hours. If coming in groups more than 4 pax, it is advisable to come after 1pm. Ample parking space within nearby warehouses.

I‚Äôll give 5 star for the food, been wanting to eat there because it‚Äôs near my workplace.
But 1 star for the delivery. The delivery man actually gave me the wrong order! I waited for ONE hour after the time he was supposed to deliver the food. üò§my parents were really angry with me as well.
The food here is honestly substandard compared to the other outlets I've been

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: I had food poisoning after eating the sushi. The food is not fresh.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Always not the same taste
But comparing with other restaurants ok
But serving staff is irresponsible

Not a high end Japanese restaurant. Taste and price wise well rounded and average if took on promotion meals. Not the freshest ingredients, but makes up for with other items. Service is good. Does seem like a good place to hang out with friends with few beers (around $10 per pint - standard price). Interior also nicely well furnished
Love it here, came more than 10x. However today, this staff called Catherine has a really horrible attitude & was too lazy to redeem our points for us. Anyway, hating on her, not the food.

Didn't expect the food to be good, but it really is! The chef does fried chicken super well. We ordered the spicy Korean fried chicken it was out of this world. The CCB is also super yummy. The CAVA burger is huge but also very tasty. My husband and I were stuffed after these three dishes due to the generous portion of the CAVA burger. For the portion, the price is very reasonable. The downside is the waiting time, it took 40 mins for us to have the first side on the table. We had to approach the service staff to check on our order. The last dish, the burger took 1 hour. Service staff is quite friendly and attentive in terms of refilling water. Easy to get their attention.
Had the beef don, ebi and fried tofu. The rice comes with miso soup. It tastes very nice. Decently priced as well!

Hi Ichikokudo! Here's my review (Food, Service & Ambience) for my dining experience today:

Food:
Ordered the limited edition Ichi-Mazesoba for a more adventurous palate. Usually would just go for the classic ichikokudo ramen but i wanted to try something different. Totally worth the experience! I loved how the sweetness from the sauce and the tanginess from the vinegar comes together. There is also a variety of texture from the crispy bits and diced onion. Really felt like a party going on in my mouth and it's really worth the try! The best part was the onsen egg, my favourite! It binds all the different elements together and combining it into one. Definitely will be back for this before it runs out!

Service:
The staffs there were really an amazing bunch! Came during the evening time and i will usually expect them to be drained but was otherwise. Welcomed me with great energy, greeted and assisted me generously and politely.

Ambience:
I was seated somewhere near the kitchen and it was nice to hear some chill music playing along. They were pretty soft... which is a bummer because i don't like silent meals but it was nice seeing the people there enjoy their working environment. I must say that most places i've been to, service crews will be just stuck one corner and watching customers as they come and go but for ichikokudo jurong point, the store itself felt alive with the vibrant energy from the staffs. It's pretty calming and enjoyable seeing them love doing what they do and still serve us greatly. It makes my experience here indeed more pleasant!

Overall, i'll be back for the yummy mazesoba and the lively atmosphere there :)

Oh!So Im not the first one to complain for tonight?
Yea!Your shop has the worst type of system ever!
I advise my customer to cancel after explaining the situation.the customer even gave me a thumbs up and agree to cancel.If not I think I will wait for 2hrs tonight and miss all my other earnings.

If you have only a few staff,remember! Customers in your shop are your priority!Not deliveries!Understand so far!?
Your shop already is so so so small,delivery riders like us crowding at the collection area you think is a good scene?

Use your brain Use your brain!
Average food. Taste is ok but price is on the spicier side. Take note they charge $1 for packaging.
Great indian muslim cuisine here !! Price was cheap and affortable. Food portion here is big too. Friendly service by staff :)

Impressed with the food and service provided. The food was decently priced and delicious. Highly recommend the coffee pork ribs and the traditional spicy tapioca rolls. The staff were friendly and attentive as well even though we came at 8pm.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Had a wonderful family anniversary celebration last weekend. The working staffs were nice and helpful.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Order for take away a bit uncomfortable as no menu to view and "waiting area" is kind of no area to wait.

Food is definately good. Will go back for the food.

Service can be improve as staff that serving food seems very tired rather than pleasant and enjoying....

Not too crowded and spacious space.

Entrance is located outside of mall.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Tried this outlet yesterday. It was almost empty during lunch time, very spacious.

The service staff who took our orders at the cashier had quite an attitude. She seemed irritated/ annoyed and was rude towards my friends even when they were very polite towards her.  She was impatient and got angry at one of my friends when he did not understand what she was saying (none of us could because she was not pronouncing the words properly/speaking up). She displayed an attitude when my friend went directly to select his choice of sides when he was ordering the double up chicken as did not know that he was allowed to choose the chicken. Oh btw there wasnt anyone behind us. This conduct is extremely turned off and uncalled for. As much as we try to understand why she is behaving this way, it is unfair for us customers to have to deal with her personal problems.

The food was affordable and tasted not bad. Chicken was tender, baked potatoes was not too hard unlike other outlets, quite nice.

The ambience would be very chill if its not for the two different songs playing in the background. One of it was probably playing from the speaker and the other one sounded like it came from the kitchen. Felt a bit uncomfortable.

Ordered the black pepper ribeye. I think they treated the piece of beef well and I enjoyed a proper medium rare steak which reflected the cut. A rare gem of a steak house in the heartlands of Toa Payoh at heartland prices.
Ambience is fairly alright, spectrum of food is above average however there is room for improvement on the cleanliness of the tables.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: yummslicious! Nasi Padang the way it should be, plenty of meat, seafood & vegetables choice. Affordable too

Ordered the items online for self-collect. Was worried about quantity so I called beforehand to ask and the staff was very kind to review my order and advise. I was updated about the order status promptly and order was available on time.  Food portion is generous and the passion fruit prawn, salted egg ribs and fish fillet with kailan were crowd favorite! Will skip the sweet and sour mushroom next time as the flour coating was too thick but overall very pleased with the tasty meal and the pleasant experience! Thumbs up! Will revisit soon :)

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Went for nasi padang (breakfast). Good spread of dishes. Fried chicken is very crispy. Only that Belachan chilli not power enough. Desserts are decent, the gula melaka gravy very sweet. üòÖ

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
A favourite of mine for jjangmyeon (blackbean sauce noodles) and tangsuyuk (sweet and sour pork) - which go very well together.

Fans of kkanpunggi (spicy garlic fried chicken) may also like to try that here; I like it although some may mot as it is slightly less crispy than other places but the seasoning is great.

Have not tried their other dishes to comment on them but an overall great place for a nice simple dinner.

Food was felt substandard compared to other branches. Less crowded than other branches but staff service was bad. Wanted to use a M mall voucher and explicitly mentioned before paying at cashier but the staff said ‚Äúnext time must say before using‚Äù and refused to redo the transaction even though we had not paid and had mentioned clearly before she keyed in anything.
Rice and the fried chicken is my fav. The chicken is not too salty or hard. Fresh and crispy!

(Translated by Google) I like his tomato sirloin casserole and fragrant braised pork ribs casserole. The meat is plenty! ! The sirloin ribs and chicken were made on the same day. Ketchup is also made by myself. The ingredients are fresh and the meat is generous. The new braised pork intestine noodle is also good. The pork intestine tastes very good, but it is a bit salty. It is just right with the light soup noodles. Next time, I want to eat braised pork intestine rice noodles. There are hot and sour noodles. But his spicy food is very spicy. You can order non-spicy or slightly spicy.
