restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Nice place for dinner...open air , cooling..nice food..good ambience..next to small lake ÔøΩ ‚Ä¶
Got the 4 dollars set. Value for money. Chicken was a bit disappointing though. Fried and hard. Sambal was good. Rice fragrant and soft.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
This Thai hotpot located in SAFRA, currently offers 1for1 thus the price is very friendly but still can only beffet-ala ka while they have only 2 waiter/waiteress helping at the dinning area... So, from order to be served, it takes.quite some time and usually the meat plates and short to serve, order the 2nd round needs to wait for 15.mins more. However 1for1.only dine in for 9ne hour... Which makes us very uncomfortable during lunch time.
The food themselves, all the those we can buy in the supermarket, the fish paste is too moistured so after cooking, the taste is very weird...
Good and almost authentic HK style roasted meat/poultry, pork/duck skin are crispy when you dine in. Once you order take away, that crunchy feel no longer there, just normal meat.
Some of the food is good and some are salty

Food here has always been consistently good. I'm not a mee rebus fan but I will gladly eat the power mee rebus here, with chicken and slathered with satay gravy. The satay itself has a very tradional taste and texture and is good as well.
Its seem that the quality of the food and the service not that good as before.The penyet rice and lontong veggies over cook.

Amazing and thoughtful customer service! Restaurant listened to the feedback given when being emailed (responded within the same day too) and the food was spectacular (both for takeaway and dining in)! Not a disappointment, even when my meat-oriented friends are being dragged along. The yam cube dessert and deep fried mushroom were the highlight of the meal!

We were there during Father's Day celebration. The service of restaurant is still great even though they were very busy. As for the food, I think the kitchen is overwhelmed, thus the standard is not as good as normal day.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: It's the decent steak house in Singapore. Nothing spectacular but the char grill chicken is always good and steak often get done a bit too much. The sides are good for kids with Mac and cheese, onion rings and pasta salad. The tasty rice is surprisingly flavorful so try that if you want some rice. One thing bad is that you need to pay for water.
11/10 Food, the only place where getting seafood with your mala is actually a smart decision. Winning free ice cream for the party feels pretty good too. Come early / late to avoid the queue!
I love this place! Their ramen is very delicious. I wish there is an add noodles option or they would give more soup for takeaway though

Order can be taken while still in queue to minimize the wait time once a table becomes available. ‰∏âÊçûÁ±≥Á≤â was good, not many place does this style of cooking. ËäôËìâËõã was below average with parts of the egg was uncooked/watery. Garlic chicken was tasty but too much non edible skin of the garlic and not much meat. Clay pot rice itself was nothing to shout about.
Great and decently priced food, it's just across nyp

I was there on 11/09/2021... my good came 1hr 30 mins late and there were four of us... our pork chop came without sauce and for myself i received UNCOOKED SNAPPER FISH & CHIPS.
My never to go to place....
The place clean,and the food are delicious I use to go every day because I stay nearby,and I suggest everyone must come and try the food.

Mutton Nasi Biryani

üçú Food wise: Overall it was a decent biryani, it had some taste of cardamon, other than that, no other fragrance, probably too light for me to taste.

The mutton was quite good though, tender and succulent meat, with a good flavor of mutton!

The taste of curry was okay, it will be better if it was spicier.

‚ú® Ambience wise: Good place to eat in. Slightly cram sometimes.

ü§µüèª Service wise: Was alright.

üíµ Price wise: $7.50
Really nice Zi Char place and pretty affordable too. Would recommend the salted egg sotong and coffee pork ribs! The signature cabbage chicken is interesting and worth trying too!

honestly the best mala i‚Äôve had in singapore, and the way they fry the eggs, potatoes, and lotus root is amazing~

overall an excellent spot for a nice lunch/dinner with friends, and i‚Äôll definitely be visiting more too!!

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Difficult to get to, food quality is good, the place is trying to cram too many tables in resulting in super narrow walking spaces which is a hazard for kids and adults. Kids tend to walk around table to different adults but it's too dangerous for a proper family meal. Also witnessed an elderly being knocked flat on the ground with her shoe coming off a distance from her. Not sure what happened but sure looks painful next to the metal trolley in the small narrow pathway. Service staff moving too fast, rushing us to eat fast and clearing the plates before more companions come. Food came very fast though. My family enjoyed the braised beancurd and salted egg prawn.
Some good food. Mainly good for the cheap and wide variety of beer. But closes quite early (9pm) and does not have many options for breakfast.

Lisa is a very good host and made us feel very welcome. The food is delicious and we have been coming back often to try the dinner buffet. The ala carte items are wide ranging and worth the value. Will come back again for another celebration üçæ

Very nice piping hot claypot with dark sauce and sesame oil fragrance. Portion is generous with rice, chicken, Chinese sausage and salted fish. Those who love ÈîÖÂ∑¥will have lots to enjoy. The sambal chilli is very good too!

Such luxuriously enjoyable Omakase ü§ó
Rich sea urchin melts in our mouth ü§§
With friendly staff and chef, complementing with the sweet umeshu, making the meal even more mesmerising ü§†
Nice India ingredients foods
Ordered the Stir-Fry Kang Kong and Marmite Chicken. Both dishes were yummy. The chilli, both belacan and sweet and sour were nice.  Service was superb! Friendly lady. :)

Went for dinner at 8pm, a quick 5 mins queue was needed to get in.

Ordered (between my friend and I): kambing soup, paper thosai, egg prata, mutton keema curry, chicken masala, seasonal vegetable, Bandung, limau ice

Kambing soup was extremely rich and flavourful! Prata and thosai were both really crispy. Mutton keema curry came in a very generous portion and was ridiculously tasty. Chicken masala was choke full of spices and you can really taste them. Cabbage was stewed to softness. Sweet drinks were decent, slightly expensive for the cup size.

Always a favourite for Indian food at yishun

Was at science centre observatory last week and couldnt forget the bryani smell that filled up the science centre compound. So i decided to pop by today. It is secluded, as u enter from the kids stop entrance even when the kids stop is closed.  Food is served hot. Ordered prawn masala, butter chicken, naan, bryani rice, tandoori yoghurt chicken. The food is refined and of good standard. One of the best Indian food with very reasonable price. The yoghurt tandoori chicken is exceptional, juicy and the full of the grill fragrance. The butter chicken is more of the tomato type and my children love it. They downed much rice with the butter chicken sauce. Very good service, as they refilled the papadum. It is definitely my to-go indian restaurant now.

As a lacto vegetarian cum vegan my opinion about this place is: These days most items are marked with ‚Äúout of stock ‚Äú dunno why. He staff have no idea about the ingredients in the sauces and the falafel balls. I‚Äôm basically a vegetarian and have eaten this falafel wrap - have been eating here for the past 2 years and I also gave a frequent diner card. Alas! They have fed me food with egg all these days.. when asked, each one of them reply differently and I‚Äôm in chaos and hunger.. I‚Äôve finally chosen not to eat anything from here except the soups and the focaccia bread. PS: this place isn‚Äôt for vegans and vegetarians if you‚Äôre looking for something to eat other than soups

Food items are very reasonably priced, garlic naan was crazily good. Butter chicken, mixed vegetables and the complimentary papadum were all done perfectly.

Will have preferred butter chicken to be in bigger chunks to add to the bite though üòä Kulfi was too sweet for my liking, Nuts added were generous! I will definitely be back!

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Variety of choice yes, price is considerably cheap compared to other neighborhoods dimsum including 1.30 dimsum. But overall food is below average, would rate 4.5 / 10 max.

First time trying this place (or perhaps I‚Äôve been here many years ago but can‚Äôt really recall). It‚Äôs located inside ITE at AMK and is really convenient for those who drive with its ample car park and location just off CTE.

The food is delicious and sizeable. The one dish that stood out was their Peking duck. It seemed like every other table ordered one when we were there. The fat and juicy skin was not lost when cut and well preserved.

It was very packed and full on the Saturday night when I went and I must say that you will definitely need to make reservation first. And oh, this is a family restaurant so it‚Äôll be bound to be busy, noisy etc. Hence I‚Äôm surprised with some of the other comments about the noise - you want peace and quiet, please choose a fine dining restaurant or Angie‚Äôs where there‚Äôs a surcharge for noisy children ü§£

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Classic tzechar stall who does great dishes like Assam fish head, sambal potato leafs, salted fish minced pork and my personal favorite salted egg pork ribs. Will come back to try their famous XO fish soup!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Love their fish soup. Fish slice is very thick and soup base is flavoured and nice. One of the best Culttlefish samba kang kong. Fish head curry, hor fun and many other food are nice too.

First visit, wasn't expecting much due to the lack of reviews, however was shock by the amazing experience. Fish is very fresh and this dish is super deliciousüòãüòã other dishes that we ordered surpass our expectations as wellüòÅüòÅ

Second visit here. Cosy atmosphere with friendly staff. The menu has more dishes now as compared to the past. We had the chicken curry with prata and dry laksa mee goreng. Both cost $8.90 each. The curry was delicious, with the right amount of potatoes and chicken. Wished there were more curry gravy though. The prata could be more crispy. The dry laksa tasted good too, with fish cake, chicken and a few prawns. The noodles would taste even better with a stronger laksa taste. I still prefer laksa with gravy. Would definitely go back for the chicken curry and nasi lemak.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
Known for the fried carrot cake (chey suay) that you have to queue for at least 30mins: tip is to place order first, have a cup of coffee, the collect.

Hawker centre is usually busy in the day, and few stalls open for dinner.

Everything is extremely slow. It took 30mins for my food to even start arriving after ordering. Half the time the food was served by servers. They even forgot some of my orders. I saw someone attempting to serve a plate to an empty table. Make sure to count your plates. There is a good chance you may have missed items.
Cheap and nice delicious food

V good hokkien prawn mee, v close to penang style. Wish soup can be less sugar. Perhaps thanks to his efficient helper hired recently, owner seems more chill, never scold customers already. Price recently increased but understandable.

One of the best tze char eatery in Spore. Highly recommended üëçüëçüëç the must tries are Marmite Pork Chop, Lobster Porridge, Cabbage Chicken, Dong Bo Pork, Sambal French Bean, Fish Maw Soup, Beef Horfun, and many others. Yums....
One of the go to place if I want to have food indulgence.. I love that they open their branch here..

We ordered their tangsuyuk (sweet & sour pork), jajangmyeon (the noodle with black sauce) and jjamppong (spicy seafood noodle). They are all delicious and at a reasonable price. Definitely will return again. They're pretty popular these days, we were lucky to get the last table on dinner time.

Firstly, we went there with no expectation as it was an impromptu visit and I didn't do any homework which I normally do. It was also to celebrate my better half's birthday and it was a nice substitute for where we initially wanted to go (Tanoshii ) but couldn't as it didn't accept young kids. Good service and nice space allowance. Nicely litted. I would give a 5 for the unagi as it really hit the spot. Don't expect a wonderful presentation like in the other restaurant. Why it is a 4 was more with tempura. It is not horrible but up to the 5 rating level. I will pay a visit for the chirashi and raw food to see if they can hit my 5 rating.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Authentic food, good service and nice environment. Will come back again!
Not bad for the food here for me and my family to order for breakfast and lunch üòã

Now they have a wide spread of food. Still love their curry bun and the heh-bee-Hiam bun. If you patronize in the morning, Bun with drink is only $2.50nett. We ordered multiple dishes for late morning and the chap chye given was disappointing, just a one person's portion. Sambal petai was good though. Well i must say that's acquired taste.
Thumbs up on their aburi saba and tonkatsu pork, nice chicken karage and chicken skin to go with alcohol. Cozy Ambience for small group gathering

Went for the buffet,simply love the food. Quite delicious some of them ended up with yummy desserts.
Staffs are very friendly. Will be back again to try more food from the menu.
Many choices of food to choose from. Food is tasty too!
Had claypot rice and sesame chicken yesterday. Delicious but not a lot of meat.
Good chinese food stall with reasonable price, generous portion, taste good and authentic

We've been here on many occasions ever since we got to know of the restaurant from Michelle Chong's social media. The Sembawang restaurant is our usual go to. There's quite a plethora of dishes but somehow we always end up ordering (not in order of preference): chilli cockles, fermented beancurd fried pork, sour vegetables fish, any tofu dish, dai lok KL noodles ÂÆâsalt baked flower crab. They have an extensive alcohol list as well, which we did not fully explore (being family occasions if I'm there) but for those interested, great place to pair drinks with their food too.
Now new Chicken Satay. Same price as Moo Ping (Pork Satay) Highly Recommend. The rest are my favourite.

Their crab very fresh! The chinese aunty taking order very friendly too!

So far, all the food we ordered all fantastic!

Highly recommended.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Lovely food and very approachable staffs. The owner is also a very friendly and courteous lady including her family members. Nice place to go for dinner with family and friends. Nara, from Yishun.

Came to this place with the recommendation of a friend. Tried their rib eye and truffle fries. Its really good! The service staff were very attentive as well! Nice environment for enjoying food w friends!
Gyu don nice. But pricey ....

A place packed with Malaysia hawker flair. Fried guo tiao is always the hot favorite with a long queue. I like the Penang prawn noodles, curry chicken noodles, bak kut teh, pig trotters claypot, claypot rice, duck rice, pig organs guo tiao and the nasi lemak stall‚Äôs chicken wing. There‚Äôs also an interesting dried version of ban mian that‚Äôs spicy.

The light snack or dessert, such as chendol, popiah and steamed bun is tasty too.

The place is also kept very clean with the highly efficient aunties who are clearing the tables.

IG: sgfood13

Awesome Traditional Hakka food!
Good service and great food!

We ordered the Hakka specialties like, the ÁÆóÁõòÂ≠êÔºåSalted baked chicken, the Hakka tofu and the pig intestine soup.

The ÁÆóÁõòÂ≠ê and Chicken is a must order.. Taste is really super.

Definitely will return to eat again if we are at Thomson area.

Rating : 5/5 stars
The pork is well marinated and fresh. Really enjoyed the taste and the ambience of this place. The matcha ice cream is yummy too, will come againüòÑüòã
Great and tasty food at affordable price. Able to make a booking on Sat night dinner and lots of choice for food.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
Went to the one in China town. It was so yummy! Pad Thai is great! Green curry is spicy and very flavoursome. Tom yum was delicious too. Great value. Will definitely visit again soon

edit; 2nd visit was good, third visit average. I won't be making the effort to go again but happy to try if passing. My opinion now is that it is not consistent and sometimes great sometimes ok.

MUST TRY! Have been visiting their outlets a couple of times since my first visit. Affordable selection of meats which might I add weren‚Äôt of bad quality. Pretty consistent as well! Would recommend the Karubi for a affordable and enjoyable meal.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Food‚Äôs not bad. Spent abt $12/person. Outdoor bbq + cool weather = best combi!
Comfort dimsum food is available here at very reasonable prices.

Definitely worth trying this ala-carte buffet Chinese restaurant and eating here again!  Good service from the staff - keep it up!  Since the food from the restaurant was surprisingly tasty, the cuisine must be pretty promising for wedding banquets.  For those who loves zhi char, the food at this restaurant is a must-try!  Highly recommended!
Nice pratas and hot coffee. Gets the job done and is open early in the mornings. Was there at 720am on a Sunday and its already opened.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Dined here with friends and was really impressed with the service. The food was decent - but the services of the waitresses - atie- was top notch. Very helpful and attentive to our request.
Very nice ambient

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: We ate between lunch and dinner, so the restaurant was empty except us. The service was very quick and the chicken rice was absolutely delicious. The waiter was a little curt, which was off-putting.

Beautiful yard seatings. Plants and even we spotted a carpenter bee around the flowers!
Don are just okay - may not be their specialty - still the price is at the high end.
Come early or very late is the key to enjoy the outdoor seatings. Before 7pm people are rushing in and the breaking of quietness breaks the beauty of the serene environment.

On the GYG website it says the sauces are "free at every GYG". However, when asked, staff said its chargeable.

This outlet used to have great service but i think they got a new manager/supervisor somewhat recently and its just been downhill from there.

Walked in, went to the counter to see the menu. This PRC waitress brings out a customer's order of basil chicken rice with a friend  egg.

The egg falls onto the counter as it was on the edge of the plate.

She picks it up with her long finger nailed hands and puts it back on the plate and proceeds to hold the egg down on the plate with her thumb as she proceeds to ask me if I'm eating here or takeaway. (In mandarin)

I can kinda understand picking the egg back from the counter and putting it back. But holding it down with her thumb on the customers plate with dirty long fingernails as she talks to me....

Not going back tho this place has the potential to be a nice family run Thai food place if it takes care of details like this.

The custard bun are still pretty good although I'm still struggling to find the best way to eat it without making a mess. Price wise can get a little steep but if you're here on weekdays then can use chope vouchers to get a $50 vouchers with $35
Food is simply delicious here. Super affordable. Friendly staffs and great chefs!

Good new experience with authentic Filippino food in this cafe/restaurant.

Affordable alcoholand bar food!
The service is really good. The person who served us is Alan. Such fantastic service. He is polite and attentive. Food here is good. We had dim sum.

Was unfortunate as one of the items sold out jist before I check out on Sunday night. The qr code website did not specify which item sold out and the staff had to make guesses after 3 to 4 times to and fro from my seat to the cashier. Delayed the ordering process by 5 to 10 mins. Mentaiko salmon sushi was nice but the app needs better coding than just showing item #3360 sold out..something like that. Coin machine was down as well.

Chicken chop aglio olio:
Chicken was well seasoned and tasty. It was also grilled to perfection with just the right amount of charring. The aglio olio looked pale and unassuming, but it was packed with garlicky taste and was seasoned enough, without being  overly oily like a lot of coffee shop aglio olios. However, personally would have liked it to be spicier.

Lousy service. So many times the staff at the AMK branch pretended not to see you even though you waved at them! Today i feel like eating Indian food so I decided to give them another chance. I went to the counter and told him I want to takeaway a packet of mee goreng and 2 egg prata. The cashier at that time was not attending to any customers but chit chatting with his colleague in the kitchen. To my disappointment he pretended not to hear me. I repeated my order and he completely ignored me! Eventually I walked away without ordering. It‚Äôs ashamed that most F&B bosses are suffering huge losses at this period but the attitude of his staff is driving his business away.
Good location & food, convenient.
Lovely little place. Food is fresh and really yummy. Would surely be back again. Visually a treat for the eyes and for the tummy too. Portions are generous. Staff are friendly and service is good.

Tasty. Samabal good. Lemak good. Kuning nice. Selar very nice. Portion too small. üò≠

Should have another price for larger portions.

Average at best. Set C came up at a total of $50.6 which is overpriced for the quality of food. Every dish there comes with an abundance of onions in them with the seafood soup with only two slices of squid in it. The bean paste noodles also has very negligible amount of meat bits in it. Sweet sour pork was also not crispy at all. Overall it‚Äôs rather disappointing.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
Excellent grilled chicken rendition of nasi lemak. Smoky and tender. The service was good on a Sunday lunch time. Sambal was more sweet than spicy but the one on the chicken made up for the spiciness. Only wished the egg yolk would be runny.

My wife tabaoed this another day but after 45 mins, the chicken wasn‚Äôt as nice. Nonetheless, 5 stars if u r having it there.

Quality of food still remains and my favourites still stay at the standard expected of the restaurant's reputation. Unfortunately service was a little tardy as the restaurant is busy and have to request for waitering staff multiple times to get condiments.
Food selection of vegetables was amazingly good. Sambal chilli is very spicy and tasty!!!

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Crystal Jade Dim Sum turned out better and cheaper than expected. ü§ìü§ì #Burpple

Food not worth your time and money.
Signature dish - Chilli Crab too salty and crab meat tasteless.
My favourite restaurant for Assam laksa and Anson Chee CheongFun
Service is really bad here. The lady who served used to be good but now they change to a guy and his attitude is really bad.

This place has been a favourite always. We went for dinner and grabbed something light (Chapathi and Ghobi chilli) with a nice hot cup of chai!

Must try if you are near Jurong East. The staff are hospitable and friendly.

This is definitely an affordable and family friendly Japanese restaurant at Jurong Point.

15 minutes waiting time for weekday lunch. Always see a long queue on weekend. The salmon is very fresh and nice! The quality of foods are similar to Ichiban, but the price is slight cheaper.

Food is ok and environment is good. Nice outdoor place for people who wants to bring their pets over to chill.

This places serves western food. Can get pretty crowded and noisy during dinner times.

A little far from MRT, but this place is worth the distance.

Will definitely come back here for more next time!

Ate halfway then realised forgot to take photo. Overall it was tasty and portions are quite generous but slightly expensive for a restaurant like that.

Fried rice - for 1 pax and 4.80 the portion was huge that it can feed two pax. However, i have had better tasty fried rice before

Cereal prawn - I think one of the best dish of the 4 dishes I ordered. Expensive but prawns were HUGE and fresh! I couldn't eat the tail part even though it was deep fried. They didn't really deep fry it properly. Not sure if it's like that but I appreciate if I can eat everything when it's deep fried. Cereal was sweet and tasty

Yam ring - I liked it as well!

Scallop and broccoli - disappointing scallops. Tasted rubbery and a lot of ginger. Broccoli was ok.

It's nice and probably I will come back for prawns if I crave. Didn't manage to try the crabs, will see how

Perfect Place for a Romantic Dinner.

Highly recommended to have a dinner here.

Wonderful Chef!

First time try. One of the best Mee Rebus I have. Thick gravy, big portion. The satay sauce addition is unique. Normal Mee Rebus is $3.5. add slice of chicken $4.5. Add a drumstick $6. Prepare for queue. Highly recommended.
Very rush to cleaning table , no one introduce menu , table small and tight
Nice good food but not enough ppl to serve, long waiting time to clear table and serve desserts despite multiple reminders... will go another branch not Safra Jurong
Very authentic! Reasonable price!

The last time I ate their Mee Rebus ‚ÄúPower‚Äù was when they were at upper Serangoon. During that time I was already impressed with their  generous portion and price at $4.50.

Now after more then 10 years, (Thanks to CNA for featuring them) managed to find them once again and tried the  ‚ÄúPower‚Äù Mee Rebus again.
This time round I am Super impressed!!!!
It is still $4.50, taste and the portion remains the same  Which is generous!!!! How can this be possible as everything in Singapore have already spiral up.

Maybe it‚Äôs due to CNA featuring them the Q happened to be pretty long,
Plus they need to chop the chicken up therefore it took a while.
The staff were very polite. Especially the store manager vwry attentive. Always a great dining experience at this branch.

Been having it for years but the visit last night disappoint me alot. Plain prata size shrinked, serve COLD curry. Ordered their mutton curry, meat taste different, slightly warm, definitely not hot. Won't be back.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: I have to say that this is the best Indian restaurant I‚Äôve been to in Singapore! Have overtaken sakunthala and gayatri on my list. Their chicken 65 is so flavourful, very well marinated. Their chicken and mutton is so soft and well cooked. We literally ate and took away for our families as well and have recommended it to everyone who‚Äôs seeking authentic Indian food but tired of Little India. Amazing amazing food! I‚Äôm in love with their food! I‚Äôll be back every week for my weekly Indian food cravings üòç

I ordered grab food just now and there was one missing item not delivered. There is no hotline to contact grab food on this except for submission through a robotic app. I tried calling the stall and the person was apologetic and arranged their own to have it delivered to me. They took the initiative to do a service discovery. Very commendable. Thank you. Will definitely support you!

Have been a regular devotee of their tempura set for the past 5 years. It's basically sushi teh quality at hawker center prices. So  reasonably priced that you can patronize every day. The boss is very hard-working and friendly don't be taken aback when he talks loud because the environment is noisy. I also recommend their salmon dishes which are very popular. Do visit early as there will be a take out queue that form during peak hours. Highly recommended and a culinary gem that showcase the best of Japanese food at down to earth pricing. üíé
I love their ramen, been eating there since 4 years agoüòã tastes as good as eating at a restaurant

They are severely understaffed. The staff tried their best, but couldnt do much. The wait time for food is horrendous. Cutlery is dirty - not just watermarks, lipstick stains on cup, leftover food on the spoon.

Food is good.

4 stars for food, 0 stars for service.
Delicious prata. Like the fish curry
This place is great! Food is pretty good, large portion, for their prices it's 100%worth it. Highly recommend! It's best to make reservationüíï

Celebrated my sister's birthday there. A total of 5 pax dining. Total about s$230+.

We ordered Peking duck, duck meat fried noodle, salted egg prawns, claypot eggplant, pork ribs, double boiled black garlic chicken soup, 3 orh nee-pumpkin dessert and 1xue er dessert and 1 mango pomelo dessert.

My mum particularly loved the Peking duck, orh nee dessert and the claypot brinja.  I like the double boiled soup.

Nice ambience and a waitress assigned to us was a very polite Malaysian lady. Her service was excellent.  The food is quite good.  I like it that it was not too crowded and we had a very attentive waitress who served us well. Will go back for the 10pax set menu in the near future. Worth a try !

Authentic Hakka restaurant tucked within Sembawang Hills, been here for more than 30 years. Upon entering you will be greeted by a cozy vibe with traditional red lanterns and maps.

Ordered 4 pax meal for $52 that includes all their signature dishes. Tea is charged for $1 each, refillable.
Hakka Noodles and Mei Cai Kou Rou on the drier side but it was still as tasty.
Spring onion beef tripe is an additional order and it was chewy with light hint of spring onions that isn't overpowering.
Salt and pepper ribs good, dumplings worth coming back for.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Been here twice, service is always very good.
Food is also quite good, very lively environment to dine in
Best nasi lemak in the world. Must try when you are visit singapore!!

Location has sufficient car park slots available.
Have many sets to choose from. Overall good quality was good. The price was reasonable too.

The chilli is a must try!
Spice up the food and everything will taste better when the chilli was added to it.

Of course, do not expect too attentive service when they are busy.

Good place to go for your Bee Hoon craving...
The staffs were friendly and attentive. Definitely a good experience

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Cozy place with amazing decor. Easily located near Red Dot Design Museum, this is the place to go for authentic Korean-Chinese food! Came here with my friends recently and they are already asking to meet up there again! Special thumbs up for the ÌÉïÏàòÏú° (sweet and sour pork)!! Set meal which consists of jajangmyeon, jjamppong, tangsuyeok and mandu, is perfect for sharing! ^^ Will definitely be back again!
Pathetic chicken rice set.. not sure how much meat in there but pure pathetic. Guess the better meat are reserved for dining in customer.

First time ordering this place thru grabfood. So glad I took a chance to try. It's fantastic, portion alot w fries crispy n seasoning just right, salad n mashed potatoes as well... Steak yummy n peppersauce shiok. Standard like restaurant kind. This stall will be my to-go steak meals.
Decent Western Food

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: A lovely mix of food stalls on the top floor (second storey) and a wet market that has traditional stalls like alteration shops and coffee beans, plus a wide selection of stalls selling vegetables, meat, seafood - all fresh!! One can even find unique vegetables typically not found at a local wet market such as kale, organic mini carrots, romanesco brocoli, and even fennel!
Gd to place to eat for breakfast..

Tried the cny takeaway with pen cai for 6 pax. The food was superb, the portion is more than enough for my family, and the service and care taken by the staff and chef was heart warming. The chef even asked if we were consuming within the next 30mins or later, and package/put in the ingredients in accordance. Thumbs up to the Chef and Pu Tien team at Northpoint.

Good food and service.
Small restaurant with ~10 tables
Not hifi, but neat and tidy with friendly staff

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Been awhile since I last visited a crystal jade LMXLB. Food wise, pretty much the same standard except for the radish pastry which was a tinge more orange and the filling was not as wet" and flavorful from what I cld recall. Service was friendly, prompt and accomodating.

Decent and affordable price Sichuan food in AMK. When i have craving for Sichuan food, this will be a not bad choice. However, if you really want good good sichuan food, i think other places can offer better.
The nasi lemak wounder full and their laksa very delicious.. friendly staff
Very worst service in this shop... Even you buy 2 coffee minimum 15mints wait not crowd also ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

I love rosti but the rosti here was a total disappointment. It was just bland and tasteless and the sour cream was a joke too! It taste completely plain, not sour enough, not creamy enough. Mac and cheese was also lack of flavor. Pork ribs doesn't have the smokey grill BBQ taste. Everything just, bleh. Service was prompt but that's it.
Food is delicious
Fantastic sandwiches! Authentic and tasty. Way better than any other burger and sandwich joints which use processed meats or cold cuts

i give it a 5 as it exceed expectation of 2.5. in malaysia, i give it a 3.

char koay teow is spicy and have wok hey. not as oily as found in penang but decent. personally like spicy.

curry mee is ok like commonly found in pasar in malaysia. should provide sambal for us to add spiciness.

Not my first time dining at Ichikokudo, but the first time at Jurong Point outlet, so congrats on the opening! I had my favorite lite shoyu ramen and it was savoury, rich, and mildly sweet too, just like how I've always liked it to be. The garlic chicken karaage and sauce was delicious. Fried ebi was a little overcooked in my opinion. Nevertheless, my friend and I had a great dining experience. Very satisfied! :) Will come again to try the other flavours!

Ridiculously slow. Management too cheap to employ the necessary staff. It's one person at the cashier, one person cooking and one person wandering around. Have to wait half an hour for "fast food". Buy KFC and join behind a queue of 20 people waiting for their food.
The nearest to me . It's cool.

Over rated in my opinion. Overall taste quite blend and not very tasty.
Came all the way from bedok but was disappointed.
Affordable, tasty and of course healthy.

Great prata place to get your prata and teh Tarik fix...
Prata is flaky on the outside and chewy on the inside and not greasy. The fish curry also deserves honorable mention.
Teh tarik really hits the spot... not overly sweet, fragrant and optimal consistency üëçüèª
Choice spot to lepak with friends....üòÑ
The sushi is good

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Good variety of Indian Muslim food, I especially like the egg roti prata and Naan.
Rude service

My current favorite place to eat in Toa Payoh. Food tastes very authentic, very spicy and numbing on my first visit couple of months back. After many visits I realized that they have toned down the ‚Äòma‚Äô and ‚Äòla‚Äô-ness, I asked and was told that they received feedback that their dishes were too spicy and numbing hence they toned them down to suit local taste more. If you would like to try their ‚Äòoriginal‚Äô taste, simply tell them that you want authentic and original level of spiciness when you are ordering!

One of the more popular Kopitiam shops in Toa Payoh. Even on a weekday night you‚Äôd have to wait 15 minutes. But the food was worth it. üòã #letsguide #burpple #foreverhungry #singaporeeats #instagood #chope #hungryeatwhat #hungryeatwhere #foodie #foodiesg #hungrygowhere #chope #entertainerapp #sgfood
My first time here, service üëç due to service charge also, some customers will give tips after paid bills. When busy peak period, slower waiting time.....me alone spend $30++
This is not the way to do business. the food is quite okay. however the portion size is extremely small, service is incredibly slow and owner turn down walk-in or takeaway based on mood.

Tried the salmon bento and fish bento. The sheer length of the salmon slice is impressive, and while the regular fish looks slightly more modest, both of them tasted fresh, flavourful, while not being too salty. The amount of fish to rice ratio was great. The tempura carrot was still crispy at the end of my meal and the soup also wasn't too salty or diluted. Probably the best Japanese food I've tried, especially at this very affordable price point of $10.50 for two bentos. Highly recommend.
Good service, nice food, very reasonable price. Ambience would be better once mrt line completed.

(Translated by Google) Serve the best fried chili rice.

(Original)
Serve the best nasi sambal goreng.

The fish head curry is good, comes with tahu goreng.
They have nasi padang too.
Crowded during lunch hours.
Nice affordable Thai meal. Tom yum is a bit sour. Fried seabass is crispy. Liked the fried tofu too. Long bean minced meat was a bit too wet.

Avoid at all cost! Whatever you ask for, they wouldn‚Äôt have. Whatever they have, you wouldn‚Äôt want to have it as it is that bad. None of the meat had any taste to it. I believe they were prepared separately and then just thrown into the gravy and masala. Was deceived by the big brand name Sakunthalas. On the bright side , the vegetarian meal and Briyani rice was edible.

Slightly crowded during lunch time. Has a wide variety in their menu, includes miso soup and a side of pickles for their lunch timing (11am-5pm). Looks appetising and amazing, however quality of the food is slightly lacking, neither good nor bad.
Tried the fried oyster, and fried noole, not impressed. I also tried sugar cane, its standard.

Doesn't matter how nice the food are, am a person that prefers good treatment than your skills. Some of the staff here always react like as if our presence are bothering them. Work on your manners. The way you treat others and your surroundings is way more important than what skills/capabilities you have.
go to spot for Peking duck! They also do the duck in other flavours such as the Ê§íÁõêÈ∏≠ which is a family favourite. Service could be more attentive, hard to get their attention
Having moved from Clementi, my housemates and I chased the storeowners to Balestier. The food prices stayed the same (i.e. very reasonable for the quality). We'll make it a monthly haunt!
Halal japanese food
Penang Fried kuay teow is the dry type with no heavy dark sauce. A little bit of spicy taste though seller says no Chilli. No cockles too. Replaced with prawns.

Mee soto and mee rebus - some of the best I've had in SG. They're not heavy on the palette after eating and ingredients are fresh. Don't forget the bergadil, epok epok (kentang‚ù§Ô∏è) and fried tempeh which are all tasty as well.

Stallholders are lovely too. You can tell they take pride in the food they sell.

(Sorry I didn't take any photo the last few times I had the food from here cos couldn't wait lol)

Nice dining environment away from the crowd and hussle at AMK central. Set lunch was a good deal with main plus drink, soup and bread at a decent price. Have always liked the rosti here which is affordable and tasty. Service was fine and will return again if nearby.
A very delicate type of vegetarian dishes that we tried in the restaurant. Refreshing menu and rather interesting. Well recommended for authentic vegetarian foods

Not as good as I thought.  Hate the pasta !  Took two mouth and I gave up. Very oily for tomatoes pasta !

Ramen, sushi and sashimi were good. Forget about hokkaido buffet.
Fish and chips was delightful!

Awesome experience! The clear Tom Yum seafood soup was just the right amount of hot and sour, they have one of the best Pad Thai ever!

Also, their fish is 50% off (fried and steamed choices available), so grab it while you can.

Sadly their pandan chicken wasn't that good.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Good price and nice place for lunch!

Very unpleasant experience dining here. We booked a table for Chinese New Year Eve for the first sitting at 530pm, for an 8 course meal. The first course arrived at 630pm and by 730pm we were only at our 4th course. The remainder of the 4 courses were rushed in the last 30mins and we finished dinner at 845pm. The second sitting started at 8pm and we were also asked to move our table to accommodate more guests. Food was average. Would not recommend this restaurant for any event, unless the aim is for a long and ardous meal with poor service. The restaurant should not take more reservations than they can manage.

Porridge was flavourful and velvety. I liked the fried wanton skin but it softens quickly so could not really enjoy for long. Porridge ingredients were substantial. Seating are stools so it is a quick eat and go kind of place. You get a 5% cashback with favepay app. Wide selection of porridge, price is alright for a shopping mall eatery. A little pricey.

One of our favourite family restaurant in SG. Staffs are all very professional, polite & leaves u a good impression. Restaurant is clean & cosy too!

Putien has seasonal menu. Other than the usual White Lor Mee, there's many other new dishes throughout the year. I love how innovative their menu planner is!

As for food wise, we always go for the White Lor Mee, Fried Tenggiri Fish, Shredded Pork with Sesame Bun, Bian Rou Soup etc. It's always sooooo good! My kids love the Fried Tenggiri Fish alot! They are always asking for more! Oh yes, I love how they slice (in cubes) the Tenggiri Fish before they fry it. This makes it easy for kids to consume! Btw they have FREE kids meal. It's a Cabbage rice with Braised beancurd & comes with a refillable barley drink.

Price wise I think it's reasonable given thar it's tasty & the portion is good for 2. I highly recommend u to Putien too!

The food is authentic and value for money. Used to travel all the way to the west for their food but this outlet is much more central. Standards remained high and service staff was warm. Certainly a hidden gem.

I like the restaurant as the chef is famous in tv, he knows the ingredients and good skills  creates a gormet meal for people to enjoy. The atmosphere is casual and relax and enjoy. The mood and place is good for dinning. I will go again.

So pricey but the food tastes horrible! Sambal sotong was so runny and bland, tasted like squids plainly cooked in chilli and water. When you look into the display, they play with colours to excite, but they know nuts about Malay cooking. If you want better Malay food, I think the one at AMK Hub's Foodfare is a better run for your money. Not the best, but at least good tasting.

Char Kuey Teow was decent. They did not allow me to make any changes like ‚Äúno chilli‚Äù. Wanton Mee was a little too sweet, but it did hit the spot. Ban mian was good, but also sweet. Chendol not quite worth the calories. May return if crave for Malaysian food again.
Good place to take away indian food. Food is reasonable in quality and price
This stall is a hidden gem! Their soup has incredible flavor. Try the dishes with bee hoon. You won't regret it!
Tried the pumpkin n yam kueh n nasi lemak, quite good. But best of all,  do the chee cheong fun,  best!  Will b back....

Noticed they changed to a slightly inner store (same row, opposite side beside Shirley desserts)
but standard still same, Rice is fragrant, chicken wing still has the crisp and tender texture (fresh),
Best tze char restaurant around ‚Ä¶ ordered their red grouper‚Ä¶ meat for fish porridge and bone for stir fly bitter gourd with fish bone..orn ni (Yam Paste) is another must eat..

Our favourite Korean-Chinese restaurant in Singapore. We visit this place very often and each time it never disappoints us. Out favourite is black bean noodle (ÏßúÏû•Î©¥) and samsun jjampong (ÏÇºÏÑ†Ïß¨ÎΩï). Service is good and price is reasonable for authentic Korean foods.
To me, the best mee soto in Singapore hands down! Didn‚Äôt manage to take any pictures as i was too hungry. The broth is simply magical and key ingredients for all soup dishes!
Flavorful Japanese Cuisine in the park, with flora and fauna surrounding the whole eatery. A must try when you finish your activities nearby at the park!

Phoenix Indian Restaurant relocated from Choa Chu Kang to Jurong East - Omni Theatre / Kids Zone to be specific. Sparkling clean new restaurant, friendly service and superb food! My friends and I have become regulars of this restaurant and we highly recommend trying ALL flavours of their Naan! Other than Naan, Butter Chicken is a MUST order!  Love their Tandoori Chicken and Gobi 65 (Fried Cauliflower) too! Not a fan of their Lollipop Chicken, though it's a good dish by itself but we felt that it just didn't go well with the rest of the traditional dishes we were having. Their Masala tea is very good too! Will continue to support this restaurant!

This is my second visit and decided to try this po pian, it is very pricey at 2.50$ and is definitely one of the top price in town. However, although the presentation looks decent, but the filling looks not packed unlike most of other, the filling is always fully packed. Also, the main ingredient, turnip are not well cooked and tasted quite bland and dry. Nothing much has put in the filling to justify the price. Definitely will not try again as you easily get a better one anywhere else. Also, the stall holder don‚Äôt even bother to ask if you need to add chilli which is usually asked by all others to avoid any misunderstanding.
Today revisited this outlet and tried the curry chicken noodle. Curry is tasty and chicken is tender. And it comes with several stalk of long bean which are uncooked. Not sure if it meant for human or otherwise.
Generally, while food wise is mostly reasonable but attitudes of the staff taking order is generally rude or at least unfriendly.
Just for those who wish to try to fried kway tew, do not that the stall only serve with chilli and if you want non spicy version, then too bad.

Perfect services and very kind indian aunty who served me. Good food and naan, especially the "papad" for all customers and i asked her bout it. When i take away my leftovers she even packed me some extra papad omgg. This made my day, and it's on my bad day. So, extra good. Haha.

Nasi Lemak is an all-time comfort food. Love the variety of side dishes offered at Sedap! My favourite has to be the steamed otah, so yums! They recently opened at Galaxis too which is nearer to me, so happy! Thank you for the good food and warm service.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Repeat customer. Good service and excellent food.

The first time my family patron this restaurant was at Commonwealth Ave.  Though the atmosphere was not as good as some places at that time, this was more than compensated by the reasonable price and nice food.

Most dishes are good, to name a few:
Marmite Pork Ribs, Braised 'Dong Po' Pork, Fish Maw Thick Soup, Cereal Prawn, Salad Fried Prawn, Homemade Toufu with Enoki Mushrooms, Prawn Paste Chicken, etc.

The current location is not as spacious as at Commonwealth and you may need to book especially on weekends. We have and will continue to go to this kitchen at their updated location which is at 126 Casuarina Rd, Singapore 579514
I'm not sure if it was my luck; the drumstick was hard and not fully cooked. üôÑ

We tried the festive coursed menu and ordered some items a la carte.

The festive menu had some really outstanding items, and some below average ones. The ice cream dessert with honey was out of the world.

From the a la carte menu, we really liked the pork cheek appetizer, and the roast duck. The steamed Chilean sea bass was a complete dud - wayy too garlicky and one dimensional.

We walked-in without reservation on vesak day evening at 5.30pm. We are a family of 4. We are lucky to be able to have a table as the restaurant is fully booked. We were told that we can only have the table till 6.30pm as they have reservations. We are fine with it. We ordered the 4 person set which is a very big portion. Ordered additional 2 white rice to eat with the Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ. Best decision. Guess which dish got wipe out by us first üòÑ. Within 5 mins after ordering , the dishes are served. Wow. Impressive. As a hakka, the dishes fits our profile, salty enough...Will bring my parents here next time.

This is newly opened in Jurong Point basement with many japanese food stores. I have tried the fried rice with char siew and ramen with char siew. Both dishes are taste good and especially the ramen soup is very thick as serving from restaurant quality.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: My favourite dim sum place in SG. Love the red bean pancake. It's the best I've tried and a must-order (a little oily but I can live with that). Also the crispy mango prawn roll is quite nice as well. Would have given it 5 star but the char siew pao tasted a bit stale today... Nevertheless, one of the best places to go if you are craving for dim sum üòã

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Tasty bee Hoon and make sure to order the salted egg yolk fish skin

The line is simply always too long here. They have an efficient ordering and collecting system so things move. Avoid peak lunch hours. Staff is nice and keep things moving along as fast as possible. Have occasionally had bad food here though. Especially the fries which is a shame because McDonald‚Äôs fries are usually so good. And I believe prices are slightly lower because it‚Äôs an educational campus.
Staff very friendly
Value for money, great food. Best to book for special occasions.

Large seating area with plenty of space.
Glutinous rice is a mushy, flavorful rice. The porridge was particularly good on the day I visited. The service is simple and homely.

I didn't get to order the Egg Tart as I would think it is overpriced for 3 small tarts.
The standard McDonald's experience within the campus of NTU. Accessible and affordable for everyone.  Only downside is the huge crowds drg peak hours drg school time.

We dined in from 12+ to 3pm and we're served by polite, friendly and attentive crew. The Manager allowed us to bring a birthday cake from external when I commended that the slice of cake on the menu was too small. It was an enjoyable experience. Highly recommend Collin's @ Jubilee!

Service 4/5
Deco/Ambience 4/5 rustic
Food 3/5
Price 2/5 a little pricey probably due to Chinese New Year

Overall 3/5
Food quality is quite good! Please make a reservation 1st as the place is quite small!
Our favorite buttet lunch
This tenpanyaki deserves a better rating. Indeed v nice, but n much much better than some in the restaurant. 1 of the best tenpanyaki in food court in sg. Portion quite big. Yummy n fresh ingredients

Came here just for the not so 'Malaysia' Malaysian food, but the claypot staff is freaking rude. I even wondered if I owe him money? or probably his boss nvr give salary?üòÇ
if you see this comment, pls don't come.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
First time at this coffee shop restaurant over Sunday morning. The food was nice and reasonably priced. Waiting time was rather short estimated abt 10 minutes, contrary to some who complained abt the long wait?!
My family and I were satisfied with the food and the service. Definitely a gem in the neighborhood where you keep seeing people joining the queue. Will come back again for sure.

Homely place with awesome friendly service with much smiles. Lots of dishes to choose from. Because there are only two of us, we ordered ala carte dishes like spicy seafood mee sua and beef teriyaki.

Love their drinks too, especially iced honey lemon tea.

Would definitely want to come back again to try the Zhi char

Waited for some time before food was served though there were only about 3 tables. We waited about 25 minutes for our food.  Staff was not attentive to customer's needs. Was busier on phone . Food was not up to expectation.  V disappointing with the food standard.  I used to patronise their shop fee years back regularly.  After pandemic,  food quality dropped tremendously.
affordable authentic thai food. i would prefer this over Tok Lae Dee in Tai Seng area
Nice cocktails and very good price for beers with satti sorru.....Nice place to visit with family and friends..

Took the signature porridge, fried bean curd wrap and the egg tarts. Egg tarts were the only dish worth commending. The rest were too salty and not half as good as those at the Canton Paradise at JEM, Jurong.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Very nice
Been eating that stall since it was open a few years ago. Never had a better western in a hawker settings.

Horrible attitude and terrible service. Will avoid at all costs. Says open at 7am buy the staff was inside and didn‚Äôt open the stall till 7:05. Yes. It‚Äôs only 5 mins but it‚Äôs the whole attitude. Customers are not considered anymore. It was raining and they don‚Äôt care about people getting wet. They don‚Äôt care and have a real stinky attitude. Really arrogant and not service orientated. Really rotten attitude. I asked when they opened, they answered me 5 mins ago which was 7:05am. They whole business stance is wrong.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Had their afternoon tea set ($10.80++), comprising of a bowl of la mian, a dian xin and a glass of milk tea. La mian was good, dian xin were horrible except for the chilli-oil dumplings. Milk tea ok.

I miss the quality of their high-tea a-la-carte buffet during pre-covid days. It was certainly worth it.

Loved this place which is located right beside GV Yishun and Murugan grocery store. They have a huge variety of options available and the taste and quality of food is also very good.
And it‚Äôs a vegetarian only restaurant. Here‚Äôs what we ordered and how we felt:

Masala Dosa meal - comes with Masala dosa, 1 idli, 1 vada and a choice of drink - 4/5
Pav Bhaji - 4/5
Chole Batura - 4/5
Samosa chat - 4/5
Bru coffee - 5/5
Badam milk - 3/5
Lime juice - 3/5
Plain dosa - 5/5

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Mookata usually not my go to food but this place serve good quality ingredients for mookata with choice of a nice spicy or a sweet dipping sauce. Best of all, you won't break the bank even if you order the whole menu.

The best food!! Very home cooked feel...
Service is tip top first class!!! Must try the Assam fish head and the clay pot wine chicken!!! Fantastic!!!
This place has seen better times. In the past, they used to serve iced gem biscuits non stop. Now, due to covid, the place is pretty quiet. The food is average now, but the portions are plentiful.

Reserved two tables for tonight dinner.
Meal serve was a bit slow due to lack of manpower, but the dishes were delicious.
May want to come again & try the peking duck.
Available at late night when other shops are closed. Prices are usually lower than other McDonald's outlets

Was there on a weekday lunch around 12pm+. It was not very crowded. The service was very fast. We ordered food for 6 people and each paid around $16.50. The duck skin is crispy and meat is soft. The char siew has a nice char and nice fat to lean ratio. Overall, it's not bad but a bit salty and has MSG.

Delicious food and excellent service! Will certainly come again!

The dishes such as Peking duck, mermaid fish, xiao long bao, rou kan salad and desserts are a must try! Very delicately prepared, intricate and mouth watering!

Service was excellent as well! Staff were attentive and approachable and Emily was great!

Thumbs up!
The mango sticky rice is nice.  In general, the food is quite good but too expensive. there are many Thai eateries which charge less and without ++.
Very generous portion! Value for money and great food! Lots of parking available too! Ordering a mini size is more than sufficient.

I was a late boomer. Never the one to go after trends amd i am easy to satisfy. So long food is in my stomach i am happy :)

Got to know about sushi-go and was totally addicted over it! Loved the varieties of sushi they have and did i mentioned the wallet friendly sushis, rice and ramens???

Must go! Now it is a place for all my celebrations. Pray tell they do not raise prices anytime soon!
Love the dessert here!

I'm always wary about restaurants or food outlets that claim to be Ipoh or Penang or Malaysian. This again proved to be the case. Food was mediocre at best. Takes a long time for the food to arrive. AC is insufficient for a lok-lok place. Also, lady boss talks too much unnecessarily. Will not be returning or recommending.
Great ambience and very attentive staff! Amazing crab bee hoon, easy to eat fried chicken. Tomato starter was interesting.
Book in advance to minimise waiting time. Food was good although the place was slightly understaffed. Will recommend this outlet if you're a safra member.

Mapo tofu is marvelous!
it's so spicy and hot but I can't stop eating it!
and there are a lot of traditional chinese foods, you must go there at once!

Ordered plain prata, masala thosai, butter chicken and mee goreng. Prata is crispy and doughy, and the curry (fish and chicken) are free flow. I personally prefer the fish curry. The butter chicken is different from what I had eaten from other places, this version is more of a dry and pasty chicken curry. The chicken is super soft and tender and the spices can be a little overpowering when eating the curry on its on, but it goes really well with prata. The masala thosai was ok, I was disappointed that one of the sauce are straight out from the fridge. The mee goreng is a miss for me.

The staffs were very friendly but they forgot to make our food item twice on a quiet morning. Hopefully this is something they will improve. Will definitely come back for the prata.
Food was fine but they screwed up having the kids meals served late and last...
Gotta try the Hor Fun (Item #14.4)
By far the best lok lok in Singapore I have tried! Their lok lok have the perfect sauce & seasoning and especially their home-made chili sauce, it was the bomb. Must try!

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Must order - oyster omelette, fried sea cucumber, cold crab and duck! We enjoyed the meal, would go back again
Ayam penyet super salty, slow service. Seems catered more for takeaways and food delivery. Do yourself a favor and head over to the Serangoon Gardens branch instead.

Huge HDB carpark nearby if you drive, took a while to find our beef, service was quick and we had the $70 Double Ribeye steak 650g (Argentina/NZ) and includes two Sapporo Premium bottled and we opt for truffle fries, also tried their home cured bacon $10. We can‚Äôt be happier, both steaks were great. Highly recommended if you are tired of hawker fare

Lots of nice Msian foods here that can fix craving on Msian food. Curry chee cheong fun and dry chili pan mee is my all time favorite. Personally feel the apam balik is not that authentic, it tastes like a kuih kapit..
The lifts at amkhub suck

Best choice of real authentic thai food! I couldn't find any thai restaurant better than them. Whenever i have the craving for thai food, they will be the 1st to come in my mind. The only place to find vegetarian spicy and sour tom yam clear soup etc. Highly recommended and sure you won't regret üòÄ

===== 2022 Jan =====
came back for the omakase (12-course).

no fancy plating, not dish by dish, but it was compensated with good portion of food items (eg. chutoro and uni.)

overall, not bad for the price.

===== 2021 Sep =====
searched Google Map for a place near Jurong Point for lunch, and found this new restaurant.

it‚Äôs actually inside TungLok Seafood restaurant and sharing the large eating hall.  can actually order from both restaurants.

the food was great, way better than i was expecting!üòãüëç

i like the most were:
a. thick and fresh Sake Sashimi.
b. crunchy outside and soft inside Truffle Tempura Prawn.
The food good staff good but the whole restaurant got mirrors everywhere, no matter where you turn can see people
I was quite torn between giving it 3 star or 4 star. It definitely sits in the 3.5 star range. ‚Ä¶

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Food is good ,but service can be bad. I think they're understaffed. So need to wait long till someone come and take order or sometimes doesn't come at all üòÖ. Must try their masala tea. It's superb. The chapati also not so bad. Quite soft.
Good food, good place and good service and friendly staff.

Quite expensive compared previous years...they mixed those not fresh prawns with the fresh ones, can tell below photos show prawns not fresh and stale...the chicken not roasted not very tasty....the louhei so-so....quite waste of money....
I came so far trusting google it say open‚Ä¶ but when arrive its close!! Come on please update system

Food quality and standard dropped compare to 5 mths ago. We missed the golden crispy chicken hence returned for another visit. But we will disappointed with the dishes that were served (coffee pork rib = meat tough; canopy fried rice = overwhelmed tasteless stale rice). However, the red grouper steamed hkg style is great, fresh and tasty today.

Have been patronize this eatery for few years. Great location besides FairPrice and hawker center around.
If you like to have your meal with cold air conditioning, and variety of Malay traditional foods, this place suits you.

I never order their other foods except their Malay Nasi Padang. Quite variety of choices, I especially liked their Chicken Merah (red means). With pick another 2 vegetable for a meal, it cost $5.80. Portion are quite big. Could easily feed 2 small eaters.

Foods cost are rising tremendously, I used to buy it at $5 for 1 meat 2 veggies. Reasonable enough they increased 80¬¢ more, as long as they keep their standard well. Hope they not increasing again.

Will only visit again if craving attacks. üòú

My grandparents purchased Cha Siew from this shop and they changed them $12 for this amount! What's worst is that majority of the pieces are burnt!

Please do not patronize such unscrupulous vendors who take advantage of the elderly. This shop is a real disgrace and having it located in the heartland (Toa Payoh) where many old folks live is even worst.

I did not even what to give a rate but unfortunately, the minimum rating of 1 star is required for the comment to be posted.
üëçüëçüëç
Crispy egg prata. The kopi is not strong but just nice for me who cant take too strong coffee. Price of egg prata at $2.40 is abit expensive though.
So so only. I was expecting bigger portion and better taste, turn out just okok only.
Yes. One of the best and reasonable priced ramen in Singapore. Worthy of a Michelin Star üí´

Had a good dinner time with family here..üôÇ

We were given a nice big booth seat at first, however due to my mum having some issues with her legs, she preferred chair seats... the manager gladly helped us with a change..üåª

Nice! Will recommend! üëç
Porridge with collagen‚Ä¶. Pricy but taste great and ‚Äúfeels‚Äù healthier after eating!!!!
Unhygienic food

Due to delays in their QR Code order taking system, customers had issues submitting their order entries, most of them had to signal to the servers to manually key in the entries. After that, some of the orders were delayed. Some of our orders  delayed, some  only arrived after the customer( who sat next to me) left. Sushi train got stuck half way for a few dishes. Staff hv to manually go and get it to the customers. Hope they resolved the problem soon.

Positive note: The waitresses tried hard to be helpful in helping us when all the above technical issues affected the food ordering and the promptness of the food arrival process. Kudos and dedicate the two stars for them.

Downside: The temperature of the restaurant was too cold and customers were made to  feel hungry and cold  at the same time. One of my most unpleasant experience as a customer.
If you would like try a different kind of normal noodle in singapore, you might want to try this noodle from yunnan. The biggest bowl of noodle soup i ever see with plenty of soup to satisfy anyone.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Value for money. Excellent location and very spacious.  Both north and south indian food and drinks available. Friendly staff. Prices are very good. Portions are good for rice meals. Quality of meat in Mutton Biryani was good. Overall it is a pleasant experience considering that it is not a fine dining place.

Amazingly good! The ribeye steak is the best, the staff is very friendly, I always feel like I am with friends when eating there. I have a serious steak addiction because of Steakgrill. Prices are also good, especially on the lunch menu. Make sure you book a table, as the place is always full. I really really recommend Steakgrill!!!
Excellent food.
Always my favourite Japanese restaurant ‚ù§Ô∏è

Very nice light Indian meal. This restaurant is  easy on the palette and makes sure their dishes are not overly spiced up. The flavours are there, briyani Rice is consistent, fluffy and flavoured. I would say for my liking it was pretty good yet lacked a slight Umph for  a South Indian Spicy food foodie like my Family. However, I would give it a thumbs up and 4 stars for service, consistency and taste.

A decent but small Thai Restaurant. Food wise I think Nakhon is Better. The spicy lemon sauce fish dish didn‚Äôt really meet and satisfy my craving. Quite crowded during dinner time. Do make reservation if you would like to try out this neighbourhood Thai restaurant. Lady Boss is friendly though üòå

Crowded during weekdays lunch time but tables are cleared quickly
I ordered briyani vegetarian set meal
Very freshly cooked and delicious
Good polite services üëç

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content:
Fresh food.
Thick sambar.
Pocket friendly.
Light on stomach.

Coffee is good here. I liked it. Something different I tried as I visit Komalas regularly for Indian Vegetarian food.
Service could have been lot better. Know how to handle the pressure please.

Boon Tong Kee is your chicken rice stall at your local coffee shop, but ‚ú® fancy ‚ú®. Food is good though, paid about $16 for a chicken rice set meal with peanuts, broccoli and also a drink to go along with it and gotta say, yummy. Only thing is that $16 is somewhat too much for chicken rice considering there‚Äôs coffee shops selling stuff similar to this for $5, but the air conditioning, clean tables and friendly staff makes up for it slightly. Overall, quite good for a chicken rice enthusiast like me.

Noodle/ingredients felt authentic
However soup was not up to par at all

Super authentic really delicious Thai food. Under-followed and with it‚Äôs jam packed flavors, we are definitely coming back here to try other dishes! Had the yellow curry seafood and the petai with prawns cooked in a unique style. Coming back! Thank you for the kind hospitality Jeremy and the team!

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
A tad bit dark - but in line with the theme of its American linkage. Food portions are smaller than I used to remember but prices are reasonable. If you are a SAFRA member, 10% discount awaits.
Quite a decent place to enjoy a Western meal but I wish restaurants like this don't charge for water. :(
Nice ambience. Food is good. Beer is strong. Staff and service is engaging and friendly. Ive nothing to drop a star. Will come back and totally recommend. üëç picture dont do justice. All is good.
Nice relaxing prata place.  Good service. Great breezy location to kill a morning.
I wasn't expecting the food quality to be so poor given their other branches are good. The service is good but the food quality itself (down to ingredients) is well below expectation.
Nice üëçchicken chop & chicken cuttle
One of oldest Chinese restaurant in Singapore.  Foods are delicious and reasonably priced. Service staff are friendly and helpful too.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Chicken Rice (SGD $6.40) @ Wee Nam Kee Chicken Rice.
.
Founded by Wee Toon Ouut in 1987, this beloved brand is today among the most popular and accessible around, serving a good rendition along other home-style comfort food.
.
The chicken has a tender, juicy, slightly springy chew, with pleasant meaty sweet savoury flavour, enhanced with a touch of salty sweet savoury nutty notes from the gravy.
.
The poached chicken is more clean-tasting with a thin gelatinous layer beneath the slippery skin, while the equally popular roasted chicken has a faint smoky aroma and a slightly crisp skin.
.
The long-grain rice is soft and loose, gently slick but not overly greasy, with lovely grainy savoury sweet flavour. The sliced juicy cucumbers and crisp spring onions lend vegetal sweet flavour.
.
Served with dark sweet soy sauce with salty savoury sweet flavour, crushed ginger with herbal sweet spice notes, chili with spicy savoury kick, and a clear chicken broth.

Talk about good value for money, this place is definitely it! All you can eat and drink on loklok, steam boat and grill. The staff are super nice and attentive. You can order using the paper sheets and also they'll come around with any newly cooked dishes. The satay is really good and the alecarte are worth a try as well!
Not cheap. I will say the price is reasonable. The quality of the ü•© and lamb shank is nice. Have not tried the rest of the menu items yet.

Good foods. Authentic Thai food. I enjoyed the food here and friendly staffs recommending the options and food serving as well.

Not so crowded for the store. The parking was quite full in the front on the store.

Price wise was ok.

Came again second time, ordered different dishes from the first one. They were delicious. The staff, same thing, was friendly. Green curry with the Thai omelet were good combination. Prawn was good as well,  easy to peel even with cutlery.
Delicious but price on the high side. You have been warned...

All is nice, the staffs are friendly.. they greeted my fam 'Happy New Year', told us what is nice and etc. But, when it came to the set meals, the price stated on the menu is clearly $4.5 and we werent told that there is an increase in price on PH(new year day).. we were only told about it after we finished our soup and bread. And the price is increased by 80cent to a dollar?!? Ok to many the price does not matter but this is actually an issue.. it is like we are 'scammed'? If my fam knew about the increased in price, we would have reconsidered the set meal.

They have a very big menu.
I particularly enjoyed the fried oyster cake, xinghua noodle and vermicelli. They also have good dim sum favourite like prawn dumpling and Xiao long Bao.
Presentation & taste of the food is good. However the staffs seems to be under and were struggling with the dinner crowd.

Ordered the bbq pork ribs and rib eye steak with garlic merlot sauce. Ribs were nice and tender, steak was a little more well done than desired, however dishes were overall value for money with generous portion sizes. I've in particularly enjoyed the sweet corn on the side. Purchase shopee vouchers to get $2 off selected dishes.
Nice.Delicious food!
The food here is superb! Almost all the dishes we tried had a genuine home-cooked flavour to them which is difficult to find nowadays. Highly recommended!

No queue and few empty tables on Sunday noon. Food served hot and made on the spot which I really like. Teh halia was good too.

Ordered tissue, plain and egg prata. Teh halia hot large. Adds up to 7.70
Limited options as compared to other outlets.

My brother visiting SG from California found this "wafer thin crispy prata" place in social media. Was there about 11.30 am on a weekday morning to beat the lunch time crowd. Just look at the long stretched prata which has a scrambled egg wrapped in it. The standard plain prata is squarish in shape. Crispy skin with a little soft texture inside. Goes well with the fish curry sauce. Kids would love to bite off the crispy prata skin.

One would think this branch in Upper Thomson is ulu (remote) and not many people would eat there. Not true. The recently opened Springleaf MRT station is smack in front of the row of cafes, restaurants, Ampang KL yong tau foo and where Springleaf Prata is. The eateries there including hardware stores, vehicle repair shops and mini groceries have struck lottery with this saver MRT station.

On another early lunch time, my brother and I had Yong tau foo. We saw one diner at another table enjoying his kuay chap and soy sauce braised boneless duck meat. Looked yummy to pass. We ordered the same to whet our appetite. The boneless duck meat was tender and salt level, not too salty was acceptable.
Childhood family restaurant! Back to enjoy a nice dinner. The western menu still relatively the same and taste delicious.

Tasty Mongolian pork rib ($15.90) & FuRong egg ($11.90) for dinner.

Portion was reasonable but unfortunately prices went up quite a lot by between 22% to 49%.

Only one waitress managing and occasionally a kitchen staff help to serve out food , so be prepared to wait.

I must admit that this waitress is superb at handling the dinner crowd; taking orders, collect payment, serving food, clearing & cleaning tables - where to find

Do not be deceived by the displays talking about the lovely steaks they serve. The sirloin I just had is literally the driest, most rubbery medium rare I ever had. On some bites, I even wonder if this is some sort of bad mock meat. The only thing I could taste was the mushroom sauce. Be warned...

Edit 4 July 2020: We decided to give JWS another chance and ordered the chicken and broccoli spaghetti in marinara sauce. This is without a doubt the worst shaghetti we had in our collective lifes. Shame on the cook who so obviously doesn't care about his/her work.

Ordered the salmon otah n their signature curry bun and it was pretty good. I like the fact they warm up the food so that it can enhance the taste. Best part is between 2.30-5pm, any bun or coffee/tea is only $2.50. Worth to pay.

content: Food is expensive and not that TASTY, they still have a loong way tooo goo! Ordered the charswiew not that great so difficult to bite. ordered a tower of beer but the dispenser was so dirty, a lot of black particles can be seen when the drink is dispense! eeew. One star is for the vibe.

The portion of beef given is also little. If you  have a big appetite then it's gonna be expensive.. 2 meat and 1 veg is $8.

Chick was good though

capturing fresh, chewy prawns but somewhat missing the spicy kick of Á∫¢Ê≤πÊäÑÊâã„ÄÇit's more on the sour and tangy side but I wished it also gave more of that numbing delight. Nevertheless, still plump & juicy

The most terrible char kuey tiaw I have ever eaten. Tasteless, dry, soggy, worst than any neighbourhood hawker centre. Totally different from the first day of opening of Malaysia boleh. Please close down if you cant maintain it well, somemore charge for sgd6.80 for this. Please DON'T say it's Penang char kuey tiaw, it's an insult to Penang people.
Rojak is nice but service needs much improvement.. Waited for an hour for my paratha, ended up cancelling the order.
Good price and nice good portion
Bought $13 sweet and sour chicken through foodpanda, and the amount given worth less than $5. If i knew i rather buy the rice set that they give more chicken.
