content: Very good Hunan food. Authentic.

Cheap ramen in a heartland coffeeshop? Where have I heard of that before? Broth was certainly thick with collagen. However, broth didn‚Äôt have the ‚Äúoomph‚Äù and char siu was disappointingly dry and tasteless. $10.90 for this is excessive. $6.90 option is probably better value.

Overdue review.

Probably gone on a wrong evening when the aircon was not working and the place got stuffy very quickly when more customers came in.

Ordered so many dishes, though only 3 of us but sad to say we enjoy none
Nice food to try out.. it suits older generation as well so recommend to bring parents or grandparents for a nice meal!
Very consistent quality, one of my favourite prawn mee soup. Love it! üëçüèª

If you like noodles, you can try here.
Mee Soup or Dry mee or Lor mee all are very nice. If you got allergy with prawn then shall not go here. The strong smell of prawn in these delicious bowls.
Always order food from here, best Thai food I've tried. üëçüèæ
My favourite lontong place in this world. The gravy is perfectly sweet, spicy, and not too thick. The lontong itself is fragrant, not too soft, not too hard or crumbly. Lontong perfection.

Went on a weekday for brunch, was a nice and quiet place to chill. Really enjoyed the pasta, which is a recommended dish . Quite a decent amount of seafood (scallops, prawns, clams) given üëçüèºüëçüèº

Spent about $195 for 5 pax for afternoon teochew dim sum. The braised duck was a bit chewy but tasty. The signature steamed chicken is also not as tender as I expected. The yam paste with pumpkin dessert was not too sweet or oily, just nice for elderly people with delicate pallette. Honestly I wouldn't say the dim sum was that great, I still prefer Cantonese styled dim sum at places like Tim Ho Wan etc. Overall, quite reasonable for the price. Reservations at least 3 weeks in advance recommended but for walk in customers, arriving after 1pm is better (less crowded) especially on weekends.
Rude owners, portion is miserable, pricey. Take your money somewhere else.
Friendly and attentive service, quality food, clean and comfortable environment. Complimentary birthday dessert a bonus.
the lady service was terrible. She has no patience at all and she expects u to know what they are offering when it's ur first visit.
Fairly good menu choices. Have the usual dim sum choices. There's also a fridge selling some of their signature food in vacuum packed ready-to-heat-up pouches.
Laksa is not bad according to my colleagues but the Penang Kway Teow didn‚Äôt meet my expectation. Penang Place Fried Kway Teow is still better.
Pretty good food. Don't reach a minute after 9:30pm if you want to dine in.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
The food is delightful and outstanding. We highly recommend three must-try dishes that are great for sharing: Sweet & Sour Pork, Seafood & Vegetable Salad Platter with Mustard Sauce, and Jjam Bong (spicy seafood noodle soup).

Ambience wise, this is not the most stylish restaurant, but is cosy and evokes an old world feel which we liked.

Tip: Make a reservation for the window seats which feels cosier and more enjoyable with views to the sidewalk.
Please try their mixed grilled is really value for money üòç Foods is nice and the staffs is very nice also, please made reservations before you come, because always full house üòä
This is the 3rd time I ask for nachos add on for the fries but I paid and didn't get .... Please always remember to put when customer pay for it

I went there during lunch time and they didn't have any prata, only biriyani, which I felt was a little disappointing since I had wanted to eat some prata.
I ended up eating the mutton biriyani here and it tasted pretty good. The serving was really big and it had cost me $8. My only gripe with it would be that there was a lot of rice and not enough meat, especially for the price of $8 for a biriyani.
Hoping to be able to try the prata if I return back there one day.
family favourite restaurant, dishes are value for money in terms of taste and portions, highly recommend the ÈÖ∏ËèúÈ±º (pickled vegetable fish, $18) as well as hotpot cauliflower!
The Food is quite good! The only thing I didn't like was the readymade prata..They should work on it! Otherwise, it was good.
Food still tasty...
SUPER COOL PLACE love the fooooodddd supper yumz i reco u try fatty bom bomü§§
Authentic thai food with fresh ingredients imported from thailand. Friendly staff that always serve with a smile despite busy period. Highly recommended
Enjoyed our dinner at Gu Ma Jia. Home cooked vibe, attentive service, friendly vegetarian options. Highlight was the yuanyang vegetable, will be back to try the Assam Fish curry!

Chicken chop is indeed nice, meat is juicy and tender, worth the four star rating I am giving. Not five star, because of the pricing, which is abit on the steep side. $7 for chicken chop, not many people can accept that pricing.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content:
First time having mookata, Surprisingly it's really good! You can either order ala carte or set. We went for set for 2 persons.
Fish & prawn is surprisingly fresh üëç I love their pork, coz it's sliced to the best size and when u grill it'll be a bit crunchy.
Their Tomyum soup is not too spicy which I like.
One of the best BBQ meat in Singapore (My opinion). Love the salad and pasta because of the well marriage of flavors üòã

Nestled in a corner of the basement of North Point, this branch of the popular eatery is not very large, but does have a few nice stalls.
I have been here a couple of times, and my personal favourites are the porridge, ban mian and the fried oyster. This time, I tried the nasi lemak, which unfortunately wasn't very good. I also noticed that the claypot rice had a long queue.
If you want to check out the place, I would suggest that you go for lunch rather than dinner, as a couple of stalls will close once they sell out.
Lovely night with my family ü§ûüèª

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Love their dumplings..their portion is rather generous and taste is good (not salty and oily). Service is prompt too.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content:
(Translated by Google) The taste is good...the price is okay...the main reason is convenience, you can buy it back to the office to eat. One-time use chopsticks, very good

(Original)

Superb aroy food gave the authentic Thai taste yum! Staffs was friendly and the bistro was cosy üíØ
Crowded eating place in Northpoint City. Good to join their membership pavkage to get good offer, such as one duck roasted and 2 x $50 e-voucher but restricted in using the package.

Standard of food dropped significantly from the first few times of our patronising before CB period; service was decent but the food does not justify the value of food paid for. Very disappointing.

As requested by owner, purely on personal taste buds and opinion:-

1) ÈáëÈæôÈ∏° (chicken with sotong paste): there was hardly any sotong paste it‚Äôs just deep fried skin with sauce. On previous occasions you could clearly see distinct paste filling. If it were for cost cutting measures, please do so without compromising the dish.

2) Ëè†Ëèú(vegetable): the vegetables tasted tough to the teeth were slightly salty and did not appear as fragrant as before. Overall, was tougher to ingest and can be improved.

3) lobster with boiled rice: the lobster meat appeared dull and stuck to the shell and did not appear as fresh. The soup was slightly fishy to the taste buds.

4) hae chor: the fillings were less crunchy and not as well done, it was previously very well fried and crispy, but on this occasion it was barely so.

5) braised pork bun: the braised pork were tougher to the bite, but overall decent, save for the bigger portions of fatty meat.
Delicious food...nice friendly staff...just tat the outlet is abit too small... overall very good
So yummy! They're really creative with their menu items. I'm so glad I tried them out. The photo is for Plaster Blaster. Their take on eggs benedict. Really yummy! üòÅüòÅüòÅ
Authentic family zi char restaurant.

Had dinner tonight during Father's Day in the restaurant. Was surprised that the quality of food in Mouth restaurant had deteriorated so much since a few years ago. All the dishes are tasteless, suppose all my overseas guests are utterly disappointed with the food. Mouth restaurant used to have excellent food in the past and it is a pity to see them in such a state now. I think the Management of Mouth restaurant should address such poor quality and improve.

Huge thank you to Mr Johnny! He is so helpful, my bubble tea was not sweet and he help me to add syrups a few time without complaining! He also explain to me about the different soup base as the kiosk did not mentioned the soup base! Thank you to such helpful Mr Johnny service crew
Great food and service - particularly good burgers and chips

I decided to check this place out after reading many good reviews on this place. The only saving grace was the chicken rendang, it was delicious. I ordered a vegetable dish (not sure what its called) that had beansprouts and green beans, it was all good until I found 2 long black hairs in it. It's definitely not mine as my hair is blonde. I also ordered assam sotong which was not cleaned properly and there were many "splinters", that wasnt enjoyable. The utensils were also VERY oily and smelled like fish and were poorly washed. Lastly, it was very expensive considering the quality of the food (1 chicken drumstick + assam sotong + vegetables + rice = ~$8). All in all, it was a disappointing experience :(

Food is great. Value for the money. The main course Saba Shioyaki Teishoku came as a set with soup side dish, rice and dessert.  I came for late lunch and was their last order. But they did not rush to cook,  the food was done well and it was delicious. One comment l wish to make was l ordered a cold Genmai cha, and l request to refill with hot cha, the waiter said it will be charged. I was  puzzled because its just fill my cup with hot tea and not cold. But anyway l know its a policy.

Besides that the atmosphere is great and cosy.

I came here today because 5 years ago l brought my late mom here to enjoy tea in a garden. She passed away 5 years ago. This place brings back good memory of my mom.

Thank you.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Could be better. My fav has always been dingtaifeng. Ahahaha..

Try again recently and their Ëë±Ê≤πÈù¢ is sooo good! Didn‚Äôt even know this exist! Will come back again for more!!!
Quite popular in the coffeeshop. My friend likes the sampal chilli the most to go with the prata.
Cheap and Good.  Weekday dine in set of 2 kosong prata / 1 egg prata with a teh is so worth it.  $3.30.  Tasty asam fish curry
Good value with great taste. Very generous with a whole chicken tigh in both mee rebus and mee soto. Satay looks more like bbq with double the amount of meat!

I shared the Tofu Omelette, Claypot Chicken and Sambal Kang Kong with two others over lunch.
It was just about right, leaning on the side where the portions were a little big. I liked the tofu omelette, it came out smelling of a really hot wok and was cooked just right, perhaps a little overcooked inside. Kang Kong tasted good. Important that the Kang Kong is young and texture not chewy. Now, onto the the restaurant's famous Claypot Chicken - chicken was well cooked through with meat falling off the bones, the cabbage was memorable, just one those good things that came with the claypot dish that completes it. Wish they had some mushrooms in the dish as it would have been complimentary to the chicken. The sauce which all of this sat in, is where I hesitate to say is really anything fantastic. It was a mild savory sauce that felt like watered down mix of Oyster sauce, soy sauce, etc. But I'd still go ahead and recommend this place to others as I think it's a basics no frills food place. Could the food be better? Of course, but its good enough to fix a hungry 3 people on a Saturday.
Place is clean and nice. Not so many people. Prata are crispy and not oily.

Ordered the combo mixed grill which is one of their signature dish. Was disappointed that the dessert I wanted was not available due to a late delivery by their supplier. But overall am satisfied with the food quality. Ample public parking but need to walk a short distance. The restaurant is also quite spacious.
One of the best Rojak sauce in town. Slightly more spicy than the others.

Ordered the Pan Seared Barramundi, sweet potato fries, truffle fries, chicken meatballs.

My main was pretty well prepared, side dishes are alright in my opinion. Meatballs were quite salty but this is subjective.

Staff were friendly and efficient!
the waiters and waitresses were kind, and the sirloin steak was good, even though it was abit more 'medium well' than 'medium rare' ':D but still very good food, definitely would come back anytime!:)
So hidden place to find ,but after you fined out you will so happy
The pork rib is like boil type with sos add on top only. The only thing ok is the fried for me other than that doesn't seen to be good.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Not worth your $ spent. Isn‚Äôt cheap

I was so excited to chance upon Mukjja and amazed to learn that this is the ONLY Korean Chinese restaurant in Singapore that makes their own noodle every day! That explains extra chewiness and authentic taste of their signature black bean noodle (jjajangmyun).

Though the typical jjajangmyun uses pork, they also serve seafood version, unlike few other rivals, so my mom could finally enjoy it to her heart‚Äôs content.

I was there on the opening week and felt the spicy jjamppong was way too spicy. We provided feedback and hope they have tweaked the spicy formula a bit.

My son who never touches any dish with sauce totally loved the sweet and sour pork. It was softer than other place but easier to chew as a result.

Highly recommended!

The best service and delicious of restaurant I had been. Last week we went to that the restaurant at Mbs, very poor service and the staffs not smiling to welcome‚Ä¶but when we walking-in this Northpoint Putie, they shown the efficiency management under the leader, provided  good services, all staffs are friendly, nicely and closely with each table . We highly recommended and definitely will be come back soon!
Claypot hicken is nice. The rest not much a fancy , other zhichar can do much better. Very noisy not a place to have some conversations over lunch

Servers were not friendly and one of them was in particular, arrogant and haughty.  We ordered green curry which was soupy and bland, chicken pieces tough - one of the worst i ever had in Sg or anywhere in the world. Tom yum soup was also bland but seafood was quite fresh. Only the kangkong was decent.  Maybe should have ordered pad thai which seems to be getting rave reviews.
Sweet and Sour Pork Rib rice with egg. Taste good too.
A good service provided and friendly staff
ice cream very nice. owner very friendly
Looked busy. Unfortunately I didn't get to buy as they don't have enough rice. I was there around 6pm so maybe end of day already to the stall.

Horrible experience from fhis outlet! Staff are disorganised, they actually forgot about my orders! Apparently I am not the only frustrated customer that's waiting incessantly long. You guys need to put in a system of checking order fulfillment to have a basic level of customer service.
Traditional western food. Love their cutlet

Loved the old school vibe that the whole place exuded, from the plates and bowls, to what the servers wore, to the interior design.

Food was authentically Singaporean. Enjoyable even if it was nothing in particular to shout about.

Dry laksa hor fun - interesting taste and nice.

Curry chicken - curry seemed a little bland. Maybe needed more coconut milk.

Curry puff - side dish from the lunch set that we took. Old Chang Kee curry puffs never disappoint.

Coffee chendol - I wasn‚Äôt crazy about it. Think I‚Äôll stick to a traditional chendol in future.

Clear chicken soup - came with the set too. Yummy. Reminds me of what my grandma made years ago.
Generous portion, reasonable price, delicious, short wait and friendly service, what more could one ask for.

Ratings
Pricing : reasonable - not cheap . Day light robbery
Service : average

Food : rice is mushy and seem to drop the standard . Food Was better when first open
Environment : coffeeshop
Delivery : average
Covid measures : ok
Pet friendly ‚ùåüê∂üêæ
Cheap Nasi Lemak stall found. Nice varieties of food and friendly staff..

Had the pork cutlet fried rice, squid rolls and Pandan chicken. Everything was cooked to perfection, while the fried rice was fragrant and freshly cooked. The secret however, is their sambal. Tinges of lime mixed into the sambal did the trick, and I‚Äôll be asking for an extra helping next time!
Staff were really friendly, and the location right by the bus stop on the ground floor really helps.
Looks like I‚Äôve found the go-to place for lunch/dinner. Prices were absolutely a bargain for the quality of food on offer. Will be back soon!

I ordered chicken cutlet and requested to replace the side dish which was egg and coleslaw with fries. My another request was to add abit more tartar sauce. One of their staff called me and said that if I want extra tartar sauce he have to remove my fries for it and replace my fries with the tartar sauce! Never seen a restaurant so stingy with a condiment and wants to replace my side dish with a condiment.  I just received the food and there is no tartar sauce at all and the potatoes salad is horrible! Definitely won't be buying from here again

This restaurant greets customers with a strong aroma and  ambience, it's nice a see a crowd again. Today it was  a sure delight to discover a giant prawn... Larger then my fingers.. So tasty with Britani and veggies.

Always crowded on peak meal hours - try going on off peak hours. I tried a few dishes (prawn mee, wanton mee, roast duck, and the chendol) and it was - I think - the closest you can get to the original. Prices are affordable (not Malaysia affordable; Singapore affordable!). Dishes are quite reasonably portioned (I get full after one dish). The chendol I thought was the best of all the rest of the food, and is the first stall I would drop by.
Completely recommend, and sometimes I have cravings thinking about it!

Food is quite good but service and ordering system can be improved. Service staff spilled raw food residue on the order receipt, no apologies. Ordering System faulty, have informed service staff and shown staff the error on the screen. Troubled him to check on order but he misinterpreted us. Later, double portion food was served and we quickly informed service staff but was faced with dispute, he called manager and said we ordered wrongly in our face. There was no apologies from either the manager or the staff, and it seems that we are the ones at fault. The food was untouched and they brought it back to the kitchen.  When we ordered food the third time through the system. Still faulty (no stock for 1 item, but the other have stock). Food never came this time. We didn‚Äôt bother about it as whole dining experiences was ruined.

Why people say it‚Äôs very nice and just $3 for the nasi lemak? Mine is $3.50 with omelette, chicken wing, hotdog, fish cake and ikan bilis. No fried fish. The rice is very wet with not much pandan taste. Is it because it‚Äôs cheap means the food is nice? I think Power Nasi Lemak is better.
Cheap and good Western food. Try the rostie.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: The Lei Cha #02-39 is phenomenal and only $4 for a big main bowl and the cha!!! So delicious!! I would say the handmade teochew pau & 88 congee is a 4/5, pretty standard.

Not the best prata in the north but still is a good prata. The rest of the food is quite average depending on the cook for the day. So the food isnt that standardise. Fast service and good value for money. The place is accessible by bus with about 4-5 minutes of walking. You could generally find a parking space here. The place is clean and the people serving are friendly.

Good food but much smaller portions compared to the restaurants in Little India. Had the masala thosai but tiny bit of potato only. The chutneys were great and the sambar was very tasty. Stuffy service from the manager but the waiters are friendly and polite.

What needs to change is the appalling use of plastic and disposables that so many local restaurants and cafes use; this cafe is no different.
Really good Thai food at reasonable prices (all nett, which is great). They‚Äôve got some decent lunch set menus too. Quite a small space so a little hard to get a table with the weekday lunch crowd.

I like the prata here because it‚Äôs really fluffy, and I think it‚Äôs better than the prata house at upp thomson.

the thosai was huge, but only came with 2 types of chutney.

great for supper as it‚Äôs open 24 hours!
Worth to try, price still moderate

Ordered the udon with chicken kaarage and katsudon. The udon portion is so small for $6.5 and the chicken kaarage is just too oily. For the katsudon, it's equally terrible. The rice is under cooked and the katsu is so oily.

I give higher than 1 star is just because that there is no queue and waiting time is not too long.
Nice neighborhood cafe with a wide variety. The cafe is quite spacious. The food were good and the staff efficient and polite

First time here. Was attracted by the Penang Assam laksa. Came in for a try as I thought most of the dishes look authentic malaysia-kl style. Ordered laksa. The soup is flavourful, however there isn't much 'liao' in it. There were little slices of sardines and some noodles. At $4.5 a bowl, thought the quantity is insufficient. Glancing across other tables, other customers were having kl noodle, Chinese style fish, fried rice etc, all looks delicious. Think I ordered the wrong item.
Not the cheapest donburi but the portion is larger than most and tastes similar to some restaurant chains. Plus point for being halal

Had the shrimp-vegetable fritter on rice. There was way too much flour and not enough sauce, so it was a very dry meal. The enoki wrapped in beef was good as usual. Service was sufficient, ambience was serviceable. ‚Ä¶

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Service was good and care was taken to ensure safe distancing, hygiene and sanitising (and temperature taking). Ambience is cozy and good for family dining. Food is OK but there's a certain fishy taste in the dumplings which is not the usual typical teepo fish taste that I'm used to. Lunch that day was just a "get stomach filled" experience. No socks off!

Service was really slow, even if it is lunch hour, I don't find it acceptable. Order taking was fast but I had to wait near to half an hour for my food to be ready. I ordered Yuan yang too, this Yuan Yang tasted like water. I think I can make better tasting instant coffee than this üôÑ FYI they use a drinks machine to dispense the coffee/Yuan yang and what not. Counter clerk did not even say thanks upon collecting payment. I need my Yuan yang from Xing wang right now!

Ordered one Roti Prata Kosong  and other with egg.  The curry is nice and tasty.  Hot soya milk not so sweet but has tinges of soya favour after taste.
For rice or noodle, ranged from SGD 8.00-SGD10. 00. A bit on the high side. Reasonable for a weekend treat.

ORDERED FROM GRAB. MISSING DRINKS. MISSING RECEIPT.

SPECIFICALLY REQUESTED FOR MORE SOY SAUCE PACKETS. GAVE 2 PACKET FOR 2PAX.

WORKERS AT THIS OUTLET SLEEPING WHILE WORKING. DO NOT ORDER FROM HERE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Price 2/5
Food 2/5
Ambience 2/5
Overall 2/5

Price does not reflect the quality of food.

Had their egg and plain prata. Flour wasn't any more flavourful than usual prata from other places, tasted like an average prata. The egg prata was freshly made and crispy while the plain prata was cold and soggy.

Curry was creamy and mildly spicy.

Had the teh halia, but it tasted more like normal teh. The ginger scent was barely there unless you focus and try your best to taste the ginger.

Place appears run-down and quite dark on the inside. There is also poor phone reception despite them offering favepay as an option. Took me about 2 minutes to complete the payment due to poor reception.

Overall, wouldn't recommend trying at all. Suggest giving this place a pass.

Bought C10 Tomato & egg fried rice at $6.90, after paying I realized I should have ordered the Egg fried rice at $5 and add tomato $1. Felt a little rip off haha. Tasty fried rice with lots of eggs and not so salty which I like. But towards the end the rice was soaked with yellow oil which was kinda off. Maybe when I'm around Novena again I will order it with less oil request.

Not your typical zi char restaurant. In addition to the regular dishes, they do a good amount of fresh seafood and the extra ordinary lobster porridge. The deep fried soon hock fish was excellent as well as the salted egg sauce crab. White bee hoon was also very good. Parking in the area may be a bit challenging but well worth a visit.

The dinning environment is unbeatable. Surrounded by greenery. We were greeted by the guy restaurant manager during lunch and he was very friendly always served with a smile. Typical Japanese set lunch that you can find elsewhere, I feel their food is rather average but all their service and environment save one star. And Their complementary dessert is nice.
The food handlers not wearing mask.
The pork gyoza is delicious and I can taste the juice comin out from the pork filling.   The quality can be compared to Japanese restaurants quality. üëçüèª

Gumajia offers delectable dishes suitable for whole family. The highlight should be their assam fish head.

Kids should love their Prawn paste chicken wing and Prawn roll.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Good selection and spread‚Ä¶ what‚Äôs best is the different chilli offered‚Ä¶ especially the red ones simply hot!  Friendly staff & good service.  Value for money.    Had repeatedly visited the different outlets as well as home delivery during pandemic.  Try it out no regrets!
Good beef rendang and ayam merah. But slightly expensive.
Great place for dim sum but make sure to make a reservation before you go. Not much to comment.
Experienced food,ambience and service all simple excellence. Thanks for extra mile service to Jasmine and the rest of the staff....Kudos‚ò∫

Had a superb dinning experience at genki sushi jurong point on 9/4/22 at 6pm. We are seated at table 41. Special and worthy mentioning of two staff namely supervisor Sean and one of the staff named janeth who warm our hearts. Sean cordially asked whether my 5yr old girl need any children cutlery without me even asking. Next my elder girl dropped the softshell handroll on the booth seat as she took from the assembly train. Janeth was so attentive and promptly informed Sean. Straightaway, Supervisor Sean offered to replace a new dish which we don't expect to as it was purely our own fault. Sean even personally check on us whether the dish had been served to my girl. We are so pleased with such top-notch service rendered to us.  Really thumbs up to janeth and Sean. They are genki valuable superstars. Sincerely hope Genki recognised Janeth and Sean for such fabulous service.

It‚Äôs my first visit here and I was pleasantly surprised by the food and service. We were seated on level 2 which was empty.

Please order the Gu Ma pork ribs! They are so delicious!!

Do make a reservation as they are famous and get really crowded.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Return visit to the restaurant! Every dish is quite unique and of quality. Would recommend to visit for families and group dining! One of my fav dish is the ice plant salad with crispy fried fish skin!
Place feel like the 70s..or Penang Malacca style..The Serving crews Ok except for 1 lady kind of high toned voice, kind of a bit impolite.

Tasty zichar.
Love the chilli gigantic crab and deep fried baby squid
Total, damage $115.40 for 4 dishes with 2 rice

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
My to-go place for Fish Head Soup Beehoon. Always comforting and portion is big. One of the better versions of this dish in SG.

But even with the quality food, it doesn‚Äôt compensate for the poor service and attitude from the staff.

I am not one of those that demand 5-star treatment at a Zi-Char stall but the service there is honestly lack-of or non-existent. I had to stand at the cashier counter, in full view of the servers, for a few minutes to get my check. And that was after I hollered to an auntie to get my bill. And apparently that auntie‚Äôs priority was to get a fish head served first and continue to hang me. The others saw and nobody acknowledged me. Nobody. Ultimately I had waited long enough to almost leave since nobody really bothered to take my money anyways. Even as someone attended to me, there was no apology or thank you. Simple gestures and none was expressed. Maybe I will do better with GrabFood or Food Panda in the future.

Had 2 Plain prata, 1 Masala chicken and Lime juice. Plain prata was crispy and not too oily. It paired well with the Masala chicken. Place wasn't too crowded and did not have to wait long for my food. Will visit again.
Delectable donburi and yakitori coupled with relaxing environment with alfresco & indoor dining. If not for its overpriced draft beers, this restaurant is definitely worth the praise.

This place proves that if you product is excellent, you don't need customer service. lol
The claypot chicken is a must try. Even my picky dad loves it.
But be prepared to be treated by little children by the staff!

Yummy üòã Traditional Beijing Duck, meat very tender. Foodwise good and fresh. Very refreshing chilled Lemongrass Jelly with Yuzu Sherbet. Great service and friendly staff... Paulin, Rui Qing and Wendy
Amazed by the unique dim sum. I ordered the afternoon tea and some dim sums. Loved the signature mee sua squares and truffle mixed mushroom dumplings‚ô•Ô∏è

This restaurant is not the usual ones that you can find in shopping malls as it is actually located inside ITE College Central nearby nanyang polytechnic as well as Ang Mo Kio and Yio Chu Kang MRT. It is fairly accessible via buses as well because there is 1 bus stop just outside the campus.

The restaurant serves traditional kind of chinese style cuisine, the ones you will normally find at weddings, zhi char style and etc. On a weekday, they serve mainly the students and teachers at eh ite and during weekends, you can expect to see more members of the public patronising the restaurant. The interior looks very classic and it resembles alot like the traditional chine restaurant where I attended wedding as a small kid in the 90's era.

Food wise, nothing to should about. I think it's really pretty decent and average. The prices are definitely on the higher side as they are restaurant based. Some of the must try dishes includes perking duck, prawns and claypot tofu. The servers and staff are friendly and will accommodate to what you need. Top up of drinks, refilling of tea were also prompt.

Overall, it's a pretty good experience and I look forward to come back in the near future if I'm craving for perking duck. You can take a walk around the school after the meal as the campus is pretty huge and no students are there during weekends. There is also a sheng siong supermarket nearby so you can shop there before heading home.
Was craving for briyani the other day and found this plc after some googling. I personally love the chicken briyani. Mutton's one was good as well. Pricing is alright. Service was good.

Unplanned visit but pleasantly surprised. Clean large place with nothing messing around walls. Super friendly and quick service. Prices are cheaper than Little India and good was good, tandoori chicken, fish curry, Butter Paneer. Tandoori roti and chapati were very thin and well made. Overall a great experience.
The best Japanese halal so far. Also cheap

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Very very poor services, very2 slow staff, have to wait more than 45 minutes for Foodpanda delivery.  Waste of time waiting and poor customer have to wait more than 1 hrs for her orders

Tried both the katsu curry and katsu don, and they are superb.
Close to restaurant quality katsu at affordable prices. Definitely worth it.

This place is great for affordable thai food. My whole meal cost $49. The steam sea bass with lime sauce is the best. A taste of zesty lime with a punch of hot chilli combination. The stuff chicken wing also taste great. The long bean with mince pork and the red ruby dessert need refinement. Thai ice tea was great too. Service was good and crowd start forming during peak hour even though it is not located at toa payoh central. Remember to bring cash only.
Good food, Good embience, but some stuff was not so friendly, cashier was so loud handling the customer on the phone. I think you need employee training.

Jubilee is a strange place indeed. A restaurant that's not really a proper restaurant per say. Looks like Safra wanted to maximise its rental income, so they simple compartmentalize the ball room into 4 sub dinning areas and leased them to Jubilee to operate as a restaurant! Good is that we booked 1 table and hv the whole sub dinning hall to ourselves. Bad is that next dinning room is hosting a D+D of sorts, so we had to put up loud noises as they had a karaoke competition for entertainment. Believe you me, wasn't that pleasant when you have to put up with extremely terrible loud voices screaming into the mike...not quite the SG got talent show!üò∞üò±

Foodwise, the quality is surprisely decent and not the usual mass produce type of food. Out of the 8 dishes on offer from the set CNY menu, I would say only the last 2 dishes....fried rice wrapped in lotus leaf n the red bean soup with glutinous rice balls are so so. The other dishes are good. Tasty and generous in portions. I liked the shark fins soup and stewed abalone with mushrooms especially! (Ok .... No disrespect to those anti shark fins activists...its just my personal choice). The prawn ball in oat flaks was also brilliant...piping hot, fresh n crunchy. The fish was humongous! Also quite fresh so would have been good if it was simply steamed instead of cooked with bean paste sauce. Still good nevertheless.

4 stars for food and 3 stars for the 'loud' ambience. 3.5 stars average. Perhaps good to visit the main branch in Katong.

If you are looking for a chinese restaurant that is  very reasonable in price, great food and good location then do consider this restaurant. The waiters and waitresses tend to be elderly but they are very friendly. If there are special functions going on, parking may be challenging. However, there is always the valet.

Friendly Thai staff, quite busy , good food
Order their garlic fried pork and fried chicken wings

Definitely value for money type of place.
Food is not bad, average but most buffets are like this - you go for quantity and not quality.
Value - for less than $40, u get abalone, shark‚Äôs fins, steamed fish, fried fish, decent sized prawns and whole lots of other choices.
Service - great people. Very attentive and really wanting you to have a good time. Staff are very stressed as it was very busy that day that I was there, but they still tried their best to accommodate. Food serving is rather slow, probably due to the crowd.
My family had a great time. Thanks for hosting us today.
Great venue for team building! Highly recommended. Thanks Kingsley for facilitating the session !!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Food are not fresh but if you just want to eat and gather cheaply, this is the place. I stopped going after the manager is cheapo and refuse to change a plate for me. Yes sure, you need to count the washing plates to earn more.   You lose your customers who visits you every other day within the week.  But it‚Äôs ok, many people still will eat at your place, you won‚Äôt close shop.

This is what you get when you wait for 20 mins. They serve grabfood order first before dine in customer. Whoever comes here please be prepared to wait atleast 30 mins for your food even though shop is not packed.

Ridiculous service. We‚Äôre the first customer and we waited very very long for the first dish that we‚Äôve pre ordered. Upon checking 4 times! With different staffs nobody get back to us to why it was not serve or why food was delayed. Will NOT patronize again.
Average service as waiters got our orders wrong but the food was amazing as always.

Love the chicken chop and cutlet. The mushroom sauce is heavenly with thinly cut fries. This food is such nostalgia and has been my old school western go to place. Shout out to all who is staying near by to give it a shot if u have not! Friendly and humorous stall owners that will brighten up your day too!

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Came to this place to try traditional teochew food and was pleasantly surprised!

Food. The standard must order dishes like the ngoh Hiang, braised duck with tofu and orh nee were good and on point. The other dishes like the drunken prawns, trio egg vegetables , I'd probably not want to order them again. Furthermore these aren't traditional teochew dishes.

Service. It's very hard to catch hold of the staff as there were so many people. My advise is to order all your dishes at one go.

Additionally, you might want to make a reservation instead of coming to queue. Very packed for a Friday night.

Totally will come back again. Very good service and the food is always so yummy! Staffs were very attentive and we're quick to top up drinks. They even bring extra continents when we din even ask for it. Love the fried beancurd! Must try!
The prata you order is made upon order,  Brayni is nice and the curry is good. Worth for money and waiting.
Their foods are so good and as a big fan of Naruto, I love their ambience ü•∞ Just that too bad they don‚Äôt have the signature Ichiraku Ramennn :(

Went there around 9am on a Sunday morning and there was a long queue. Most of the people buy in bulk of 5 to 10 packets! The worker is very fast but because of the high volume, you still need to be prepared to wait for 20 minutes or so.

We ordered the nasi lemak and also the curry puff (3 pieces for 2 dollars). Not bad - crispy skin and tasty generous fillings. Took a photo with a standard rubik cube for size comparison.

The nasi lemak rice is fluffy and fragrant. The fried ikan bilis and peanut is very fresh and crunchy. I like the chicken wing too - crispy on the outside and the batter is very thin so you are still eating the chicken wing and not the batter :p.

The sambal is the sweet type but lacking in omph. That is the reason for the 4 stars instead of 5 stars.

Liked it. Good value. Guo tie was cheap and large portion.

#localguides #heartlandfood #goodvalue
Good taste like eating in Thailand, cheep price but big portion... highly recommend.

Three of us went there yesterday for lunch. Contrary to what some reviewers said, we found the service good. The set lunch for three is more than enough for three adult males. The popular signature dishes are indeed very tasty and the dessert Oni is one of the best we have tried.

Grateful to Cecelia but left because of peer pressure.  The kitchen is very unsafe both because the management does no business in improving safety and pricing of items sold . I judge the whole entity as a failure..well in disguise and in perceiving that the big boss is too arrogant and too flamboyant to the shareholders and only thinks highly of the brand which is not even original in Taste.  Japanese people will tell you this whole set-up is corrupted to a certain extent and there is going to be a dispute soon from logistics down to distribution networks. In fact the NEA is going to task and remove the label from the kitchens of UMISUSHI. Appreciate your concerted effort in making the disorganisation review and help throw the disputed managers out to the public and private eateries for further questions.
Repeated customer, always my to go for china foods. Have tried many things over the menu and always was impressed! Delightful services and affordable prices! Highly recommended!!
Daphne did very good job and we are very happy with the quality of food and friendly service. Thanks

Introduced to this gem Muslim hawker, find their mee Soto, mee rebus and satays very delicious, affordable and satisfying. Hawker very friendly.
If I happen to pass by noticing no queue, will certainly eat. They sold out before 2000h on my last visit. üëçüèªüëçüèª

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Cheap and good!

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Good cheap lunches at L1, but most sold out by 1pm.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Probably the BEST MOOKATA in SG....GOOD FOOD , GOOD MOOD!
Nice little family style Chinese restaurant. Typical Singapore dishes prepared just like home cooked food.

My child wanted to try out, food is very average, not enough staff on Sunday.

Long wait to go inside even no one in front of us, ordered a green tea also need to keep asking the staff .

Love the gyoza kimchi nabe, the soup which is a bit spicy and sour makes it a perfect match when you slurp it hot. The salmon teriyaki is juicy and it mix well with the tomato and cucumber. The lobster salad and ebi sushi is still my all time favourite with their generous wasabi serving.

I enjoyed the chicken momo, especially with the sauce (not sure what it is). I wish they can create the Bhutanese version with cheese ;) I miss that chilli cheese momo in Bhutan. The meat in both main dish 'Chicken Tash With Pulau' and 'Nepali Lamb Choila' are very tasty üòã Hub said he went there with too high an expectation (he had actual nepalese food on himalayan mount before) so he wasn't too satisfied but I enjoyed the food üòÑ I think I will return üòã Anyway it seems like western food is more popular here. The western food serving looks generous and great plating.

The service is tip top. My table serving waitress ÈùôÈõ™ service was professional n warming! The rest of the teamwas caring and always ready for any request. Great place to spent the evening with family or friends.
Excellent service from staff Berlin! Having buffet here with a very reasonable price. Surprisingly all the food was amazing and delicious. Look at the pic!

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
I love Indian food and used to be a big fan of Anjana, I recommend to some of my friends and the love it too, the service and food was great on my last visit back in 2021.

I pay my visit again in 2022, and feel like I'm in a totally different restaurant. Service was bad, especially one of the young staff that no wearing the uniform.

I ordered butter chicken naan set, and see this is what I get, the portion much smaller than what I had previously, and they served white rice instead of nasi biryani because they run out of biryani. You can inform your customer up front so that we can choose another option, but no, they service you with white rice and when you question them, they answer impatiently.

Won't come back again with this kind of service.

Lamb is overcooked, over salted. Pork is drier than the desert. Chicken thigh is basic, salty. Fries are soggy, presumably big batch, then it cooled down. Onion rings are under. Chicken wings are bland. I don't recommend.

Horrible experience with their membership system. My friend and i each of us apply as their member to enjoy the 10% discount plus $20 offset after we heard that we can split the bill and enjoy the discount and offset.

When we bill, the manager told us the system got problem splitting the bill so we only can use one member account.

Would recommend if anyone want to enjoy the benefit ask them split the bill first before signing up. You need pay through paypal first

Will come back again as i still got $20 worth of points to use. Overall the food is nice for the price but service can be better.
Wow. Absolutely delicious

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Fast service and yummy food

Thanks to Covid-19. We‚Äôre only able to do takeaway. But since every restaurant is only able to do takeaway. They are competing among themselves with various deals & promos. Boon Tong Kee is no exception. They have some of the more value deals in the market. At $8 plus GST. You get boiled chicken, veggies, a meat ball & a side (fish slices, Thai tofu, prawn roll, meat ball, salad you tiao or pork belly mui cai). Not only this they got various other deals available. Check out the website. Thou their online service is really not up to standard yet. Some inconvenient as it‚Äôs not that 100% process.

The mee rebus was pretty good, the sauce was tasty and a bit to thick for my preference.

The gado gado was just alright.
Tried out the chicken cutlet. Feels like the cutlet is just a thin slice of chicken meat flatten and fried. Not really worth the price tagged to the dish.

Good and cheap everyday goto restaurant. Food is pretty good but not the best heng hua I have tried. No aircon and seatings are very tight.
Prices and pretty cheap, my dinner of 7 only spent less than $95 - we had some 8 dishes.
Bee Hoon Soto Drumstick. Probably Ang Mo Kio's central most famous Mee Soto stall and I only recently realise they actually have a drumstick version for the anti shredded chicken person like me!
Slow service. waited 15 min to receive my first order. food quality is poor.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Nice place to eat at night... Can get alil crowded sometimes... Good friendly staff now...

Nice western food at reasonable prices but seating arrangements are very bad. All diners seated back to back with no safe distancing measures. Not a safe place to patronise during current Covid-19 situations.

I must agree that Boon Tong Kee‚Äôs chicken is tender and good but then the service at Ang Mo Kio branch is really slow on all my 2 visits. For take away 4 packets of standard set order placed at Sunday 4.50pm had to wait for close 20-25 mins.
Very good

Interesting Nasi Lemak! Good choices available. I like the flavour of the rice and it's chicken. The combinations is interesting. I do find it a bit pricey but they make up with taste. Will try again when possible.
Not bad their sweet potato fries was good. Spinach soup reminded me of Jack's Place.

Very lovely ambience for a relaxing dinner. friendly staffs whose services are really awesome. Food was marvellous in terms of taste as well as presentation. Food portion is big and value for money. I'd suggest to order bit by bit if you're not much of an eater. Definitely coming back again with my family

The Japanese food street concept is really great where you can enjoy quality Japanese food in a food court style as well as pick a restaurant of your preference to find more in elegance. The good is not all authentic, but the standard is close enough to the genuine ones in Orchard. The price points are around SGD10 for a set meal for an individual.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: First time visit here on weekday, food was tasty especially the sauces, if u like spicy, this is the best place to try it, price is affordable.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
The deal was $35 NETT hotpot buffet with free flow drinks for 2 all day everyday! (OK, so the third of us paid ala carte lo ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è)
‚Å£‚Å£
Great service never goes out of style, thank you Shidah for keeping us as happy as our tummies! Our meal won't be the same without your friendly chatters and recommendations! Red Tom yum broth is a must-order! Love their Thai milk tea to accompany the meal, and we highly recommend the fresh fish paste! I'm hooked on the chicken cheese balls too and lost count how many I ateüòù‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Å£Shidah's cheery disposition really rubbed off us and kept us happy throughout the meal! Thanks Shidah!

Meat was sparse and there is no price list displayed throughout entire shop. You will only know the price after you ordered. $6.5 for this plate with no add ons. Nothing special but charge premium. Be warned
Used to go here often.  Lunch time can be crowded

Bento sets are value for money. Staff are efficient and work as fast as they can. However, sometimes the queue can be held up because customers in front have very voluminous orders. So take care when ordering.

Environment is typical Chinese settings with modern twist. Area is quite limited so do make reservation. Food wise can be quite salty and oily but taste is good. Each dish is nicely presented. If one thing they can improve is probably their customer service which I find lacking in terms of friendliness and attentiveness. Otherwise it‚Äôs a good place to visit, especially impressive place to go for meat-eaters.
Tasted satay so ummphlicious üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªand same goes for the kambing  soup!

First time 'seafood noodles' only had 1 seafood item - sotong. Seafood means minimally prawn and sth else but not even the sth else. Omg and it's $14. Quite disappointing. And the sweet and sour pork is not say very tasty or special. It's just normal. Zhi char has better kolo meat I feel. We always see queues during weekends. Now I don't understand why.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Well if guy's happen to be there, please try their roti prata, it really really very nice, i love it so much, whenever i go there, i always order this, is my favorite

Had lunch delivered over the weekend and 4 out of 5 items turned out to be below par. The plain naans were fine. The fried rice and the 3 side dishes, weren't, and this was not just a single person's opinion, but the consensus from a group of 6! Portion sizes weren't too big either and wouldn't be considered bang for your buck. (To make matters worse, I think the food might have given a few of us, including yours truly, an upset tummy).  2 stars for on-time delivery and decent naans.
Came here to attend A wedding lunch, foods not bad but service is not so good maybe lack of staff, just A few serving almost 100 peoples.

I can never have enough to say about TMC.
Customer Service - TIPTOP. Fast and personal.
Food - Fusion and put together very well.
Ambience - The Windstedt Branch is by far my favourite. Very bright, cozy, family-friendly, and simply GORGEOUS.

The Beef Ribs Roti Kirai
Braised short beef ribs, glazed and homemade secret ingredient sauce serve with roti kirai
$39.00
never disappoints.

The cakes, where should I start.
The Ondeh-ondeh, the chocolate cake, all melts in your mouth.
Not too sweet, just nice.

The owner Hafiz, and the staffs are all very friendly.
And we even got a free slice of cake for birthdays and anniversaries.

The price is quite a setback but for the price you pay,
you will definitely get every cents' worth through the glorious food, ambience and service.
Every Wednesday morning they serve a special peanut congee. It‚Äôs very good.
Awesome service! Very friendly and attentive staff. Food portion is reasonable and good.

food quality and ambience is similar to other branches.

tried mexican cola for the first time, the sweetness is so distinct, it‚Äôs not my favorite ü§ó

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Ok ok lah. Whilst fried stuff was decent the rest was so so incl Char siew sou. The century egg porridge was a big disappointment. And service was so so..
The prawn noodle is really, really excellent.  The chilli paste is authentic Penang style. This is a must try for all food lovers
Celebrate Christmas here, the meal is delicious, the ambient is nice, the service is good.. Overall satisfied :D

We came by for lunch on Good Friday holiday. Ordered the signature steam chicken, yam ring with sweet & sour pork and spinach. All dishes were well-executed and flavourful. Service was good at this outlet. Advisable to make a table reservation on weekends for indoor seating. Price was reasonable for the portions. Happy to be back again :)

My go to place of my kids want prata. There are stalls selling you very nice, crispy, and oily prata. There are stalls selling below par soggy prata. This stall serves prata that's just right - crispiness within softness. It's not overly oily too.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Very good food and reasonable price. High ceiling for indoor seatings. Service good too. Alfreso dinning.  Mask off!!!

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Saw their Ala-Carte Buffet on Facebook and me and my family wanted to try. When we reached the restaurant we were told that it was full so we were sitted at the outdoor area, there are oil smoke coming out of the top of the building every 10 mins, and we got choked multiple times by it. We came at about 6pm and waited till 7pm and there is only chilli sauce on the table, we were served the fried squid, but we believe that it belongs to the other table beside us. We continue waited until about 7.30pm and i start to have gastric. And there are still no food on our table. Ended up we gave up and went off. Totally wasted all my family time for coming down. We kept asking for the food but the waiter kept pushing to us that they are short handed and there is also a lot of table waiting before us. Understand that, but if you are unable to handle this much customers then you should not have accept this many customers and even offer ala-carte buffet. And also, since you have advertisements on facebook, you should expect more customers coming right? This is my worst dining experience ever. Totally BLACKLISTED, come at your own risk. üò°

The place is conducive, something different from normal western foods, portion is big at a reasonable price. They have wines and other foods from Nepal for light meals and also cakes . Coffee is also nice.

this place is highly raved and recommended by my cousin who studied at ntu! it was my first time having soupy mala xiang guo and i must say that im quite impressed! the scrambled eggs and fried potato/lotus root made the meal a surprisingly unique one, except the fact that it wasn‚Äôt numbing at all which a typical mxg should be? hence one star off fr that inconsistency. that aside, everything was fairly good and i‚Äôll probably return again when craving hits!
Spent 50 dollars for 4 persons, including zhajiang mian, pork rib ramen, jiaozi, dumpling noodle, tsingdao beer... Good value!

I live nearby this store and patronising frequently. The rice, chilli, ikan bilis, peanut, chicken wing etc are very nice.  Curry puff very nice as well.  Queue could be quit long and to ensure you get all the topping you like, you have to come in the morning.
Authentic taste
Steam fish very fresh and well cook I like it,will go back to patronise again.

The way Chinese Dim Sum meant to be served. Fast & efficient. I love that they have the same menu on the weekday and weekend. It gets really crowded on the weekends so come on a weekday if you can. You will not miss out on any items.

The porridge was particularly good on the day I visited. The service is simple and homely.

Enjoyed my meal there.
Decent spread of Japanese food. Sashimi is fresh. Personally felt the sushi rice was a tad too bland. Service is good in general. Won't mind visiting again

This is the review of the shop that sells coffee. I ordered coffee. The person who took my order repeated the order to the cashier so as to let her know how much to charge me for it. However, instead of  giving me coffee, the person who took my order gave me tea. I went back to the stall holder to inform her she gave me the wrong order. Instead of apologising for her mistake, she insisted I ordered tea. She even interrogated me like a criminal if I tasted the tea. Unbelievably rude. I will not patronise this store ever again.
Food is v bland n not tasty.  There are better places with clean food,  tasting much better

Pretty decent food. We ordered the hot&sour soup, steamed dumplings and the cheese fried dumplings. Hot & sour soup was tasty but not that spicy. Loved both sets of dumplings! Fairly reasonable prices for the area too.
Food is generally good, the Bbq pork a bit expensive. Will come back to try the staff‚Äôs highly recommended dinner buffet

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Not bad food, though service kinda confusing coz they might not be the most meticulous in ensuring what they have served out tallied with what we ordered.
Place kinda warm coz outdoor eating.
Nice food, finally found the closest KL Hokkien Noodle in Singapore

Favourite place to satisfy our Indian food crave. Bustling place with the aroma of the curries, chatter and the shouts of service staff orders filling the air. Service is always fast here and you will be in and out within 45 mins.

Love the fluffy white rice here, doesn‚Äôt stuff you out like other places. Masala dishes are all hits but the dry ones are more intense in flavour. Can‚Äôt miss dishes are the butter paneer, which is Indian cottage cheese and spinach.

Parking is sufficient but be prepared for a wait during meal hours and Sundays.
Nice casual dining setup. Good food and good service from the staff.

We've been here twice now. They serve a tasty range of Sichuan/Chinese fare including dim sum. I recommend their Sichuan-spiced roasted chicken. Note that some dishes can be extremely garlicky. Prices are decent for a hotel restaurant.

Pop by for lunch by myself since I am in the area. Staff was polite and patient. Ordered the set lunch of Pomodoro Pasta with chicken skewers. Add on the mushroom soup. Meanwhile my phone battery almost flat, they really tried to find if there's a suitable charger for me. Appreciate that! Soup came and taste good with fragrance of Truffle oil. Could be better if it's thicker. Main course came, pasta is cooked just nice and 3 skewers of tender chicken in teriyaki sauce.
Very relaxing ambience, good service and nice decent food at reasonable price! Will come again, keep up the good work
Good food, music, and vibe for a mookata at Toa Payoh. üëçüèª
Worst service
Restaurant quality Japanese food at food court prices. Great value for money. Great quality of food. You can take the quality of the ingredients.
Prawn mee was tasteless, asam laksa was so so, doesn‚Äôt even have pineapple. Not worth the price! Won‚Äôt visit again!

Small family restaurant with a limited menu but we loved everything we had! They only have 8 tables and only do two sittings per mealtime so definitely make a reservation. High quality food at friendly prices; you can really taste the love and care put into every single dish - the xiao long baos are freshly made upon order so expect to wait a little.

You'll only have one chance to order so I suggest to order more than you think is enough ;)
Really really rich tonkotsu broth at an affordable price point. Honestly up there with some mainstream ramen chains. Highly recommended!

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Coronation Plaza outlet at level 3 food court ... excellent value and service. Deservedly popular, attracts lots of students from nearby tutorial centres. Very competitive prices. I particularly like the fish cakes, and mixed fried veg with prawns. Mango salad always fresh, and they will omit the chili for sensitive western palates like mine üòâ.

Food quality is quite good, but just take note of 2 things: (1) price for rice is ridiculous ($2.50) if you buy less than 4 sticks of tori. (2) during peak period, the calculation of items may be wrong as they have to do it very quickly.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: I was initially skeptical about the Thai food here. But my clean empty bowl at the end of my meal should paint a vivid picture to the quality of the food. Nothing more than authentic.
Really good good across the board, nice selection of Sake, and some good drafts too! Worth every bit of flavour. Enjoyed the friendly and attentive service as well!

Jajangmyeon is very good and the serving size is quite large. The service standards at this restaurant surpass most others: the staff pays close attention to your dining experience and would attend to you automatically. Dropped a chopstick and they will automatically pass you a new pair, automatically replenish the side dishes, ask you whether you'll like raw onion to go with the food etc. Will come back again for the jajangmyeon and good service.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Mediocre food, pad thai tasted like soy sauce. Not worth the long wait and putting up with the unfriendly service.

sharing this info from my mum and my aunt , they went to eat at tpy branch on the 4th of aug 2022, they had mango sticky rice, my mum told me that she complain to the waitress that the rice is hard, like its from the fridge or freezer then heat up in the microwave., as my mum ask the waitress, when was this made,  was it fresh? the waitress replied and said this : it was made like 2days ago, the current chef who made it wasn't there that day 4 th Aug. . so made it in advance and store in the freezer or fridge, and heat it up in the microwave. *CLAPS MY HANDS*

can i ask u , thai Lily, is that how u made all ur food in advance and store it in the freezer, or fridge and reheat it up in the microwave? i tell u, if i was there with my mum , i confirm have have diarrhea immediately, Well,, if u wanna up keep ur restaurant, and to maintain good reviews, please do something about ur food being freshness. if u cant do or cook that certain food, pls 86 it.

oh btw the way the timestamp would be around 12 to 1pm.
thanks.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Very nice food and very friendly people üíö..am recommend to all . Must try.

Very good food that tastes like a home-cooked meal at zichar prices, in a homely restaurant that harks back to 80s or even 70s Singapore. All the dishes my group of 4 had were delicious: preserved vegetables with pork, red wine sauce prawns, salt-baked chicken, yong tau foo, Hakka fried yam, even the basic broccoli. Service was prompt and attentive. There was no GST or even service charge! We'll definitely be back soon.

The restaurant also prepares bento boxes for takeout for only $5.80. If only I lived nearby.

Went for lunch.
Had saba fish and beef meals and sotong from different stalls.
Good food and cake for money.
Will go back again.
If you stay more than 3 minutes after you finish eating, a staff would discomfort you, saying wants to clear the table while she is staring at the waiting queue despite 20 minutes of eating.
Alhamdulilaah...not bad, good location, food affordable prices. Next door macdonald restaurant, and multi storey car park above.
Superb tasting food.

Srisun Prata is one of the more popular stalls in the coffee shop. They offer variety of prata and tosei. Nasi bryani is available and so are kambing soup and even Ayam Penyet, a version of malay Chicken rice. A good place for your lunch or dinner but be prepared to queue. Weekend queue is always longer.
Great service, nice place for ramen and dons. Filling and tasty food enjoyed the smoked duck ramen and the dons, quite generous with the ingredients.

Ordered Little San as takeout lunch. Selection for sushi was reasonable.
Service was quick. It was spacious inside but not too many seats.
Best prata ! Super like the fish curry sauce
Generous portions and chicken cutlet that was not overly oily. Sambal has kick.
The stir-fried Jajangmyeon tasted alright and I think they can do an option so that you can order a smaller portion for cheaper. The ginseng chicken soup was great üëç
Love every aspect of this place! The cute robots, the fun interior, and of course the yummy food (esp the thick cut sashimi). Plus points for keeping the kiddo entertained with the robots...

Soup Restaurant @ united is pretty good. The staff there are quite service pro esp the uncle but it is chaotic on busy nites. Food is tasty and consistant. You can eat big as in group or many dishes or small but be prepared to order double or triple portions for a group as some dishes are small ones. Any soup of the day is fine by me and if you're hungry the full platter of white/steamed chicken slices will help fill you up easy, I love the ginger paste it comes with. The steamed minced meat with salted egg n water chestnuts is a winner in my books.

(Translated by Google) It's delicious, it retains the original flavor of the food, which is rare. (It's not just Sichuan food)
Not suitable for people who taste too heavy/can't taste the food & don't go if you don't have good economic conditions.

I'm Quite Impressed w Their Food Crispness & Freshness... Their Sauces Are Served Hot~ Too!!!
wonderful meal. first time enjoying mookata. The season meat plus d premium beef is superb. Chili is spicy enough. thumbs up

Made reservation. Double confirmed my reservation when asked again.
Arrived at tamako and was informed that "we are full". When asked for waiting time, "must wait for tables". So, what's the point for double confirmation of this reservation with no tables??
Tamako has become Cannotgo. Even waiter went to hide inside the cashier.

I‚Äôve visited Paradise Hotpot a couple of times ‚Äî it has a similar concept to Beauty in A Pot / Haidilao except each person has their own little hotpot. It‚Äôs also has a similar price point as the two other restaurants stated above, but the difference is Paradise Hotpot offers a really great promo (40% off the total bill if you dine at off-peak hours), which makes it quite reasonable.

I don‚Äôt have any complaints about the ingredients. The seafood and vegetables are fresh, and I also enjoy the innards (eg kidney and liver). My favourite soup base is the pork soup, but I‚Äôve also heard good reviews of the beef bone and chicken soup!

Service staff are attentive so that‚Äôs a plus. Overall, good atmosphere and good food, and a pleasant experience! I‚Äôll definitely come again.

I can't rate it any lower than 5 stars when the food is a 5 and service level a 6, can I?
I had my meal there just a few days ago and will not forget the incident when i accidentally dropped one of my chopsticks. It landed with a faint sound. I could not see where it landed so i decided to continue enjoying my delicious meal of egg fried rice with a spoon that was on the table. To me it was a non-event. But before i could continue with my meal,  a service staff appeared with a pair of chopsticks and placed it right in front of me. I was totally stunned. The food is better than other mamak food in Yishun and the price is reasonable.
Annoying staff with rude service.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: The Dim sum average taste . Missed those good old day at The Neptune Theatre Restaurant was a well-known restaurant and theatre in Singapore that was in business from the 1970s to 2006. Housed in the Overseas Union House at Collyer Quay, Neptune was famous for hosting topless revues and large-scale dinners. During the day, the restaurant served Cantonese dim sum fare that was popular with the office workers in the area. (Text taken from inforpedia. ) üßäüßäüßä

Expensive like HELL.
Terrible experience.
The plates for all dishes are ladies' palm size. So you can imagine that how small is their portion for every dishes.

Radish Omelette $9 - So basically it's just 2 eggs (maybe it's rooster egg that's why $4 each) + few onions + very few radish. Radish omelette without radish taste.

Thai Kang Kong $9 - Imagine that you request 2 portions from mixed rice stall equal the portion this shop served to us. (maybe the Kang Kong import from Thailand lah)

Belacan Pork $9 - The portion same as you order 2 portions from mixed rice stall.

If the portion match with the price won't feel so dunlan.

Good vibe restaurant. Clean & comfy, food was served fast on a not so busy weekday afternoon
Mapo Tofu = Good taste, authentic not too oily compare with others
Grilled sliceFish = Fresh fish, fresh ingredient
Rice = Fragrant rice, not the usual dry/cheap type
Awesome one

super good experience at tanoke. came on a public holiday and despite the crowd, service was on point and attentive.

the food we ordered all came at a good pace. serving was just nice for my family, but for big eaters may feel their rice bowl & sando portions of be a little small. the food were all well seasoned and very nicely presented.

For dessert, our favourite is the panna cotta followed by smores tart then the shiso lychee sorbet (although it is quite a good palette cleanser) likewise for the yuzu ice cream (i recommend it)  üëçüèª

Overall, would definitely return for another meal ü•∞

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: The service was really pleasant.Food was delicious and fresh. Chappathi, Naan , and the best is channa..!!  Good place .. nearby Jurong East MRT and in close to International business park ..  they can cater for all events .. the meal experience you won't soon forget.

Got to know this place when my friend bought me my birthday dinner in July this year. Since then, I have revisited this restaurant at least once a week unless I am out of town. Captain Wendy Wong remembered me on my 2nd visit which is a week apart from the first, and has been providing personalised service by addressing me by my name and take note of my order preferences.

A chain tze char outlet which you can find across the island. Though not all outlets serve good food. Affordable tze char fare along novena. Nothing to shout about but its definitely above average. The restaurant was considerably filled on a Sunday night at 8ish when other restaurants were closing for the day.

If you're in the vicinity and looking for some tze char, I'd recommend this restaurant.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Delicious

Was at their woodlands outlet. The can drinks are not chilled and they only provide a cup of ice per can. And on a hot day, if the ice has melted before you can finish the drink, the drinks stall will not give you more ice nor sell you ice. Probably the first time encountering such incident. So best is don‚Äôt drink or be prepared for drinks not chilled.

A very well maintained, clean and spacious restaurant within the University campus.

The service was good... and the dishes were very tasty.

The food took a little longer to arrive... perhaps this can be improved. But it was worth the wait.
The food is delicious and prices are affordable. I am very glad that there is this restaurant near my place.

Love their bakery. Freshly made on spot.
Beef bourguignon melts in your mouth. Do take home a loaf of bread to enjoy at home. :)

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
This is to share my personal experience with GrabFood Singapore on Friday 5 July 2019. The food I ordered from GrabFood is from ‚ÄúHua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice & Noodle (Sembawang Outlet). It is located at: Blk 463 Sembawang Drive, Sembawang Riverlodge, #01-01, Singapore 750463. This food store have several branches in Singapore.

I ordered a whole roasted duck as well as 1/2 kg (500 grams) of Char Siew via GrabFood at S$ 40.50 Nett (after using a S$20 Grab Coupon) for my family. When the food arrived and my mum open the packing, she found that the Char Siew is ‚Äúextremely little‚Äù and suspected something is amiss. She then contacted me and I rushed home to attend to the matter.

I then took out my ‚ÄúDigital Weighing Machine‚Äù and found out to my horror that the Char Siew only weigh ‚Äú360 grams‚Äù. I contacted Grab Hotline and was told to file an ‚Äúonline customer service support‚Äù, which I do so later.

As the food shop is nearby my house, I took the whole food package and paid them a visit. The shop staff don‚Äôt seemed to be bothered to my complain and directed me to call their person-in-charge (PIC). After several attempts, the PIC finally answered my phone call.

The food menu has indicated 1/2 Kg (i.e. 500 grams) for the Char Siew and why I am only given 360 grams? This is a shortage around 25%.

At the end, the food shop finally gave me a ‚Äú300 grams of Char Siew‚Äù as a ‚Äúmake up‚Äù after a long wait around 30 minutes.

This case shouldn‚Äôt have happened. It is unknown and remain a question mark whether the food stall staff or the Grab delivery boy has short-changed or taken my ‚ÄúChar Siew‚Äù initially. A lot of time and effort have been wasted on this matter if the related party are sincere doing business ethically.

Nice and fresh meat. Great beef, Good cut and well marinated. Good BBQ system with no smoke and no smell. Great portion also for that price. The mushrooms also very nice. price is slightly at the high side S$17 per person. Very clean restaurant. If group dine in, they won't allow incomplete group to enter into all has arrived. Clean restaurant. Was half full during a weekday evening 6pm.

Mutton Briyani is honestly a little disappointing at this price point. Rice was lacking in flavour and the mutton was mutton cubes.

Prata was also small and cold. They did not even bother reheating before serving.

There are definitely better Indian food elsewhere..

Lao Beijing moved from Velocity to Square 2. All the favourites in the menu still around.  The new place have more spacious seats. Service still good. Recommended items - Mermaid, bacon bal kwa with Sakad, salad Prawn with melon and walnut, egg white fried rice with convoy, fried French beans, black garlic xiao long bao and for dessert - Red bean pancake with ice cream.

What an enjoyable experience! Sure some kinks here and there, not perfect, but definitely has so much going for it that I wholeheartedly give a 5 star review!!

The manager was warm, attentive, very genuine and friendly. He explained the composition of each dish and also the beginnings of the restaurant as a scale up from the previous gastrobar.

Went there to sample the restaurant week menu.

The yellowtail is to-die-for, one of the best that I've tasted. The cook on the lamb was so good, it was tender and had none of the gamey flavour, although the marination could be improved to impart more flavour.

The sirloin was so good, the marbling so rich that it melted in the mouth and hardly needed any condiments to accompany it.

Desserts probably could be improved further. The s'mores tart was overpowering in it's sweetness, there really wasn't much else going for it. The matcha panna cotta was so much better, and well matched by the tart was of the raspberry jam.

The yuzu sake recommended was spot on and was delightful in its citrusy flavour and subtle sweetness.

This is a restaurant where the whole is greater than the sum of its parts. Hope to see this restaurant grow from strength to strength, and I will be back to sample again.
Awesome japanese bento and ramen organised like kopitiam.
so so..quite disappointed in some take away.. need to be serious on their food taste

Good variety of food & drinks available. Had only 1 friendly staff, a Chinese women the rest were kind of in their own world even there was only 2 group of customers present. Avoid sitting near entrance as my food was fested with housefly. You would enjoy this place if you enjoy spicy food and alcohol
Cheap and authentic Xin hua cuisine.

The service was ok. However, the food was pretty low quality. I had a 50% off voucher and I still felt it was overpriced for what it was. After reading the other reviewers maybe I should not have ordered the steak.

I could understand order don't come in their order number sequence but mine was no.380, 3 plain pratas take-away. Then came after me of 8 orders: 4 cheese pratas and 4 cheese with eggs for 2 different set of people dine-in 383 and 384. Earlier 381 and 382 had also had collected their orders of other itemsqqa1q1.  When I confronted the manager, he argued that plain was make differently?! Isn't it with putting cheese and egg on the dough or plain dough right? What kind of logic? He could also argued that plain needs 3 min and ingredient take 5 min. So those who came in later, dine-in, paid more for their food can get to serve first then my order of 3 plain pratas and take away!? I was there the whole 33mins which based on his logic and well organised arrangement - bravo!! Conclusion, demand for your order when it is next in queue.

Chanced upon it at ITE Central, during the open house today. The waitresses were professional in noting my mum's allergies, and were polite. The dishes were presented beautifully, and the food was great. Wouldn't mind coming back again.
Nice and cool place for great food and drinks. Located inside Safra Yishun.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
Don't try to eat after usual eating time
arrived at2.30 told me that they open at 4, only later i realize that opening time on the wall
I suppose they don't wanna open fire juz for 1 customer?

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: A good efficient dinning place that serve good standard chicken rice and assorted food at reasonable prices. Set meal are good option for a full meal. Here the chicken is tender and sauces are on par. Dumplings soup dumplings are generous in fillings. Dining ambiance is good enough and air condition . You go , order , eat and run.  No frills.

Felt the pricing is quite steep. Have to pay 80cents more for milk, and add on for rice/noodles. Taste is above average, and people pay more for the ambience and ease of finding seats. Prawn rolls are good though as a side dish. My colleague tried hor fun and it also felt quite ordinary.

Food is good but was so disappointed with the service. Its Mother's Day and I understand that they will be busy but when I was ordering and asked about how long it will take, they told me ot will take 20mins. I was willing to wait. But after 30mins, they still tell me sorry, waiting dor one more dish and I was still patiently waiting until its 45mins. I went to the kitchen there and tell them I've waited for 45mins. And they said sorry but do I still want my order, they are really busy. How can 20mins become 45mins? And they came up a few dishes in 20 mins and a few dishes in 45mins? Just very disappointed. No matter how good the food is, service is very important.

Always had a good meal here; although the queue on weekends are pretty long, they have an efficient ordering system, food is usually served less than 5-min upon order placed. Prices are quite steep with a Murtabak costing $9.00 but portions are generous.
