During this Phase 2 (HA) wef 22/7/2021, this stall still operating from 6am. Nasi padang plenty choice of dishes. Best breakfast & lunch takeaway.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
First time trying Korean Chinese food, so can't comment much.

I would say the food is 70% Korean and 30% Chinese.
Food is ok but expensive

First time there so it's first impression review. Both my wife and I were very  satisfied with the Gindara Cod stew that my and the Tuna bowl.
Food is at least 4 stars, and value for money with the 20% discount as we ordered before 7pm on a weekday

But service is 3 stars at best because they appear shorthanded.

Lots of Japanese clientile that looked like regulars.

Ordered ichi-ramen (original) with kaarage (set) and hokkai clam ramen. The soup base felt bland and was not hot. There was an alkaline taste with the noodles. The other ingredients, e.g. bamboo shoots, black fungus, felt cold too. The "onsen" egg was a huge disappointment. $4.50 for the add-on Kaarage set was also disappointing as the portion was very small (~abt 3 small pieces).

Hard to get attention of servers to re-fill the iced and hot green tea. The iced green tea was also like room temperature.

Through the dinner, there was also a pestering fly (we were seated at the booth seat area). This was also highlighted in other reviewers' comments.

Felt over-priced for the food and service quality.

-2 stars for the poor food experience.
-1 star for the lacking service.
-1 star for the pestering fly, which we couldn't wait to end the dinner and leave asap.

Definitely will not return.

PS: This might be an one-off incident, and maybe other food options on the menu could be better. Saw some customers ordered donburi dishes and they looked not bad.

Empty tables available but not letting people in. Purposely creating long queue. If they are understaffed, management should do something about it. Having a queue outside with empty tables in the restaurant is ridiculous!

Dined a couple of times, on weekdays evenings and weekends mealtimes it can be quite crowded but weekends 3-5pm it‚Äôs rather empty.

Food üçΩ
Recommended dishes are:
- roast pork belly/ bbq pork
- XO carrot cake
- signature bbq pork bun with boluo crust
- congee - so smooth and delicious
- HK milk tea - served in an iced tumbler, very creamy and full of flavour
- Cheong fun (rice rolls)
- glutinous chicken rice wrapped in pandan leaf - it‚Äôs a small portion so just nice for one to eat

Ambience and accessibility üïØ‚ôøÔ∏è
Have seen plenty of elderly in wheelchair coming in and restaurant is spacious thus definitely accessible. They will even help to shift the chairs to make way for wheelchair to slot into the table instead. Have baby chairs and also booth seats.

Service is generally pretty attentive and welcoming. Do note the nuts at the start are chargeable so feel free to reject if you like. Wet tissues are also chargeable.

If you have a Citibank card, pay with it and get $10 return voucher with $50 min spend. Weekdays 3-5pm diners can also enjoy 40% off dim sum

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Friendly and attentive staff. It was my husband and my first visit to this outlet at Toa Payoh. They really deserve a 4 stars (cleaniless, attentiveness, friendliness etc). We will definitely go back there for our next mookata session :)

Ordered several dishes, if I recall about 6 dishes only. Each time a dish is served, the next takes 15 minutes. That‚Äôs fine, but what is totally disappointing is the lack of quality in our food. The crab was bitter and slimey and the meat was either too salty or underseasoned.

Rather than keep up a facade of a finer dining experience (interior and atmosphere really reminded of a wedding dinner), perhaps they should look into improving the quality of the food instead, just a suggestion.

Best Thing Here: Fried Fish Skin, Peanuts
Avoid: Everything Else

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Pretty lackluster but still edible. You probably have other better choices in this coffeeshop unless you are craving for some dim sum
Nice charred rice with plentiful of chicken meat
Great food, love the pork cutlet. Lady boss very friendly
Muslim Indian restaurant. U all the Indian food available. Nice customer services.

I order pattaya rice without veggies takeways, he said okay and did it. I open the pack and obviously i cant see the inside because its covered with eggs and i trusted that they did it correctly but turns out theres a lot of veggies inside when i checked the inside at home. Do they hear the order correctly?

We ordered the set menu for 6 comprising, crispy fish skin topping on salad with sliced baby abalone, shark fin in egg broth, steamed promfret, prawn with tofu broth, vegetables with mushrooms, and yam paste dessert. We swapped the chicken dish for sliced goose meat snd ordered an additional dish of teochew fried kuay teow with diced spring onions snd crispy fried pork lard.
Very generous portions of springy noodles. The "bak yue pok" is always crunchy and flavouful. The handmade fishballs really good. Slightly chewy and not too bouncy. Noodle sauce quite unique blend.

I love the prawn noodles there. Soup is rich and sweet with spice. I understand some may said Uncle attitude isn't good. But for me, I just order, eat n zhao. So don't think too much on that, he won't even remember you if you come once awhile like me.
Great for snacking with seating available if snacking on the go is not your thing. The Bee Hoon with beverage is a great bargain.
Campus price point. Approx $1 -$2 cheaper than the malls.
Deep fried pork was really good, don't forget to use the sauce. Prices were around the standard. Would recommend! üëçüèº
Situated inside Bishan Park, nice place for a good Japanese meal.
Food was great! Repeated customers of this restaurant, always love to go back to try their dishes üôåüèª

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
1 of other stall within the hawker centre offering same dishes of ü¶û ü¶êü¶Ä white bee hoon.

Not as good as other stall.
Good place to eat. Nice environment. Good customer service ü§ó

Very frustrated today. Bought this Indian Rojak at Ministry of Rojak at Northpoint which total came up to $44.40. When asked for more gravy (gravy was given so little not even half of the tie plastic).
Got scolded(loudly) by the staff who doing the cutting n packing.
When made pymt i ve told the cashier who's also taking order that pls give me more gravy n she said ok. But this male staff was so rude didn't want to give yet grumbling. Felt so angry.
What a terrible service!!!!.

Food is awesome. And service is fantastic. It's really good for family gathering or reunion with friends. Ambience is good. They have a karaoke system for a great time. Wide variety of food to choose from. We ordered fried mantou too. Thumbs up!!!

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Nice..

The stall name is not prominent, so if you miss it just look for stall number #01-59.
I ordered the teriyaki chicken bento for $4.50, very reasonable priced for  Japanese food. The teriyaki chicken pieces rested on a bed of tempura crispy flour with drizzled sauce, chicken taste soft and nice but to me is not marinated enough. The rice is probably Thai rice version with salad and a bowl of soup. The surprise touch was the freshly fried tempura carrot slide, nice and crispy!

I walk to the next aisle to finished off my lunch with local cold grass jelly with sea coconut dessert, yum!
Pork Shabu Shabu set with fresh meat cuts and vegetables. Good broth and sauces. Friendly and efficient staffs. Cosy, comfortable and quiet environment.
Love the deep fried potato slices! Decent mala to have

Murugan idli kadi is the best Indian restaurant in Jurong east area, its very near to Jurong east murugan temple, best in cost, you can customize your food according to your needs and price, everything is fresh food.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Duck rice and char siew is not bad, but the meat given is a bit lesser.
Had to wait almost 45mins for a prata, and it tasted average. Owner needs to reconsider the manpower deployment during supper hours. Not recommended.
Nice place good food.
Stuffy, warm, not much stall. Most people are waiting for their takeaway order.

It's located on the 2nd floor of a shop house. The ambience is good. Staff is friendly.
Food is nice & the salad is fresh. Australian Striploin bowl is my favorite. Pork bowl is also nice.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Prata was good with fish curry. Freshly made when u order. They make thier own prata dough unlike most prata shop, factory order in a box. Lots of varieties. Will try their Thai menu and Briyani when come again.

After the recent renovation, they removed the soup sets from their menu and replaced it with "hot food" which you can ask for combinations of pasta, fries, vegetables, fish and meat (like an army cookhouse with more choices).

Unfortunately, the "hot food" is nothing but hot. I ordered falafel with fries and vegetables but everything was cold, hard and unappetising.

A very regrettable choice for lunch; I could have something cheaper and better at any of the other restaurants beside it.

Good service and good dim sum. including the porridge and carrot cake
The push cart is on during weekend for better efficiency.
Better enjoy during weekday
Their signature dishes are mostly good  with ngoh hiang fritter, braised duck and fried hor fun

Came on a Friday night and it wasn't too crowded. Food and drinks came across as rather mild compared to other restaurants but it tasted healthier too, so I'm quite okay with that. Price is affordable as well. Would come back again to try the ramen.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
LOVE THE FOOD!! Set for 2 costs $53++. Can choose 2 bowls of noodles (jampong and/or jjm), tang su yuk and 5 dumplings. Idk where to begin....i rly love the food here.

The jampong was full of seafood flavour and lots of seafood given. About 4 or 5 mussels, prawn, octopus. Noodles were of great texture. The jjm was light and not jelat at all. Managed to finish the entire bowl.

The fried dumplings were crispy. The tang su yuk! It was served freshly fried. And even when it was cold thru the meal, the pork and batter did not turn hard. Finished it too!

Omg i feel like eating it now.
One of the best around!

Decent Indian food but a few peculiarities like minimum order of 2 crabs is a must at $14 each and complementary veggies with the rice is given free only once in small portions. There was potential but totally turned off by the way they do business.

The $80+ crab was huge, full of eggs and very fresh. The mantous were had an almost crispy skin and soft white insides. The kai lan was yummy, not old, soft not chewy. The cereal prawns were large and fleshy. Overall, definitely a recommend. Only thing is the chilli crab gravy loses out to the one at Casuarina Rd.
Authentic nasi lemak at a very reasonable price
Service was prompt. Food is as expected, delicious and fresh. Limited seating due to distancing requirements so go early to avoid crowds.

One of the best sake tasting I have been. Waitress and Waiter service is superb excellent. Thanks Iries & Nareen. Excellent place and very tasty lunch. Must try
Thumbs up üëç

Had dinner buffet with my family last Saturday. Worst experience ever. Thought of giving this a try even though the reviews were not good. There's only around 7 tables for buffet and some tables I believe it's under the tour group tables (set meals mostly I observe) but the staff arrangements is so disorganized! The supervisor or is it manager I am not sure,keep giving instructions to the waitresses but this particular waitress probably new, keep serving the wrong dishes to the tables and she accidentally knocked over the hot tea at our table which thankfully didn't scalded my dad.After the first round of the 7 dishes(served one time only) second round onwards they just keep forgetting about us. Until I had to asked the manager /supervisor then they serve our dishes out. One of the kitchen server ( she's not in uniform but white t shirt) came out and saw our table is empty and said oh dear I will check for you with the kitchen.One of the fried dishes was cold when my folks bite on it,another dish was the long beans and was already very soggy("old veg" not my words,but the supervisor/manager's )  At $46.80++ the menu is not extensive and some of the dishes are not served even though we asked again. So tired of waiting and chasing after our food. The food is nothing to shout about and seriously is it because it is buffet so we shouldn't be requesting our food to be serve warm and cooked nicely?

The jjamppong and jjangmyeon we ordered were really delicious and noodles were cooked to perfection. However, I have to say that the taste has been adjusted for local taste buds. The jjamppong would have tasted better if it was slightly spicier and had more "wok hey". We ordered their fried Mandu to try and finished everything as well.
No hygiene.  Lady mopped floor, without washing hands, used thongs and hand to push food into plastics for packing.  When mentioned, showed attitude.

Just brought a mutton briyani, give me 6pcs of mutton bone with minimum meat attached, very bad, I thought I order mutton bone briyani instead of mutton briyani, also charge $7, I cannot say is expensive but not worth it, because you are eating mutton bone with little bit curry with rice, 1 hard boiled egg & little vegetables, better go to the opposite store, more honestly with the food you pay for.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Simply the best. Better than all the rest. A bit more expensive but that's inflation for you. Good chutney. Great with thosai. Although there is no difference between plain, butter, and ghee dosa.

Love the food here but the service is not great..... came at 8pm and waited for 10 + mins in front of the 'please wait to be seated' sign before a service staff approached us and said that they were full for the day and cannot accomodate us. they said that they thought we were browsing/takeaway so they didn't approach us which is... super passive???? we didn't want to flag them also because they looked super busy walking in and out serving people, and they also sat and attended to another group before us that was also waiting in line but they ignored us... anyway food is great though but come early/make a reservation and make sure to be forthcoming when you arrive because the staff is not üò¨üò¨üò¨
First time here and it was a really good experience. Really enjoyed their food and you can hardly find food stall using charcoal to cook their food. Will definitely come here again.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Very clean and very good service. Food is up to the standard you expect from Astons.

There is a long queue when I went there so maybe that's something you would want to keep in mind but the queue was quite short.

10% discount for HomeTeamNS members but if you are Singaporean, I'm sure you know that ü§£

Budget type of ala carte buffet... Where you get to order as much as you want for those dishes that you always never had enough of during wedding banquets. Haha.
Prawns, chicken, whole fish etc...

Bought take away tako, only squid as they dont have prawns. The squid is very small in portion. Tako taste is just right but hopefully next time the fillings should be better than now.
Staffs quiete friendly. Will be back again next time.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
I happened to choose Fathers' Day to have dinner there with an old friend so there were two seatings for reservation: 5.30pm or 8pm. I booked for 8pm. We (group of six) were seated in a hall at L2. There weren't many people though i heard the restaurant at L1 was full.
The food was delicious. We had braised duck with beancurd (Âç§È∏≠ÊãºË±ÜÂπ≤)Ôºådeep-fried ngoh hiang (‰∫îÈ¶ôÊû£)Ôºå Teochew steamed pomfrey (ÊΩÆËí∏È≤≥È±º), Teochew Puning fermented-bean chicken (ÊôÆÂÆÅË±ÜÈÖ±Ëµ∞Âú∞È∏°)Ôºåwok-fried mee pok with braised duck with X.O. sauce (X.O.ÈÖ±Âç§È∏≠Èù¢ËñÑ) and yam paste desserts (with hashima / slice of pumpkin). Two persons complemented their meal with a bowl of rice.

As my children were allergic to prawns, the waiter quickly came back to us when he found out the ngoh hiang contained prawn (he thought it only had pork).
My fav was the fish, and my friend (who hadn't been there for  quite a while) particularly liked the fried mee pok (i thought it was unusual too cos it's usu fried mee). The ngoh hiang was crispy and fragrant The yam paste was good (smooth, not cloyingly sweet or oily). Staff were helpful.

All in all, it was a pleasant meal.
Satay was delicious ,soft and tasty.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Havent prepare food but they took order. Waited for 30 mins just 1 meal. Subpar service.

If can I wanted to give 0 star to this shop. Order briyani chicken sambal, chicken curry and fried chicken for take away, told them to separate the curry from the rice but when wanted to eat it, my rice is as wet as ocean and sambal chicken only taste spicy not even salty or any sweetness.
That rootbeer, when serve is not full, stingy, potato also ,need to dig it and taste like normal, not recommend, won't come again.
Steamed fish with lemon sauce was overly sweet. Pork belly was soaked in oil and over sweet! It's like eating sugared pork skin. Bad experience and will never come back again.

Led by celebrity chef Heman Tan, Szechuan food is yummy and authentic. Ëæ£Â≠êÈ∏°was nicely cooked, not oily and spices and spicy level just nice. The eggplant was amazing nice, crisp on the outside and soft and tender on the inside, coated nicely caramelised.
Very good and affordable mee rebus.
Nice seafood congee the taste is different from other seafood congee must try hard to describe juz try it

Went for Royal Rumble, $6.50.  Comes with Dish, chicken wing, begedil, otah. They used basmati rice, slight fragrance. Sambal a little spicy, good. Begedil also good. Fish ok. Chicken wing a bit crispy, not flavourful enough. Egg is runny which is usually overcook. Otah tasted soso. Overall very decent plate of nasi lemak.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Saw the good reviews here and decided to try. But Honestly, I found the food very mediocre. I thought jjajang was alright, but I felt Dong Fang Hong was much nicer. The Jjambong was very very average tasting..

However, I agree that the noodles used for the Jjajang and Jjambong were very nice and chewy and it is their pride, despite the sauce and soup being pretty so so.

Tangsuyuk was alright? The pork was pretty tough and not really marinated thoroughly. Mandu was also average..

I think overall for $50++ for set A.. I think I rather patronise another stall based on taste of food alone. But service was good and quick.
Very good food at reasonable price.

Ordered on deliveroo. Missing rice and metal scrap from dish scrubber found. Tried to contact restaurant to remediate but was put on hold without informing and waited very long with no response. Will proceed to submit case to SFA
Prata was very crispy. Curry is tasty. Long Q on Sunday but short waiting time to get table. Fast service. Chicken bee hoon is delicious too. Will come back to try other menu.. woohoo
Nice Indian food, but service was normal Indian style. Not much people there and price also reasonable compare to other India restaurants.

Ordered wild mushroom pasta in cream sauce. Mushroom was ok. Pasta texture was ok. But too much cheese added n it was crazy salty. Maybe I'll try something else next time or ask them to put less salt or not put cheese.

Food court Japanese yakitori don eatery. Simple food (while  a tad lacking in authenticity) but  reckon its good enuf and suffice for a quick meal. I had the Japanese premium beef rice bowl. The beef was a tad overdone but still OK. Could have added a bit sauce while grilling as the whole rice bowl is slightly on the dry side.
Great authentic Thai food . Great service also . Highly recommend

We actually already had lunch but since we were around the area we had to stop by here anyway. Was last here before Springleaf was awarded Michelin guide! Surprised and glad to see the pratas are still really good quality and the fish curry they serve too. We had the premium egg floss prata which was a little over $5, though it's not the cheapest prata but the portions was huge and servings of the curry was amazing and of course unlimited. Definitely will be back again and again (to other outlets as well of course!)
Got hair in the soup and the staff tell me ‚Äúoh hao, no worries‚Äù ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
I have been finding the satay and Mala fish taste like this for a long time..really really nice.even my grandpa said üëâNo Complaint with the taste..price are affordable üòçüòçüòçüòçüòç

It was a beautiful Sunday and my friends and I decided to go for Thai food after our hiking at Macritche Reservoir. One of our friends decided to bring us to Velocity where she was frequent at A-Roy Thai Restaurant. We were there at 11am where the restaurant was just open. We were ushered by a friendly waitress and directed our seats at the corner. First impression counts though. I was pretty much happy the way the waitress welcomed us, so much poise and professionalism. The ambience was nice and cosy. I ordered the Thai Milk Tea and I love it so much. The flour just right and not too sweet. We ordered 3 dishes which they are beyond delicious and authentic. Love the Thai foods here...definitely you must try! I shared some pictures of the foods we ordered. As a whole experience at this A-Roy Restaurant, I will give 5 stars.

If you wanna eat here, you gotta come early cos queues can get pretty crazy within an hour of opening. Great food at super reasonable prices, in a low fuss setting. Service may take a while when things get busy so be patient! Expect endless chatter from big groups, so forget about intimate conversation. Just go, slurp loudly, eat with gusto, order and order some more, order to bring home for supper and enjoy the experience!
I like their fried rice. Portion is good and taste ok. Not the best but in amk area, its quite ok.
Delicious nasi padang. Good items finish early. Long queues at lunch

The waiters/waitress were friendly and helpful.. Thank you for the good service given to my uncle and aunty who are regular costumer of srisun. . They love going to Srisun.. And will come again next time when I visit. Thank you

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: I want to respond to hock seng on the 27th. He serves very well and is very enthusiastic. This is my first visit here. Thank you for introducing the soup and food. I will come back next time. ü•∞
Worst service ever. Problems in bringing wine, problems even in changing plates. Service staff could complain and argue back with diners. I cannot fathom how a restaurant could operate like this.
Not bad. Curry is typical. Rojak is okay.

Chui Xiang Kitchen never disappoints. Their staff are friendly and their lobster porridge is to die for. A pot of porridge is enough but their other dishes are great too that my friends and I always end up ordering more and overfilling our bellies with great food.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Great food great taste great service.

Malaysian-styled Fishball noodles at 158 Ang Mo Kio Avenue 4.

Many of my close friends know that I don't like eating Fishballs (except for Old Chang Kee's giant ones). Don't ask me why.

Ok. Back to this gem of a stall.

Queues usually start forming at around 0730H, and by around 1030H, they'd be sold out and that's it.

The sambal and sweet sauce combination is like how you'd shower a Muse with, throw in some Harp tunes and you're in Xanadu.

Taupok bursts with so much soup that it puts a good Onde-Onde to shame. It is swimming in a vat of hot soup, waiting to be served.

Fishcake is soft on the inside. Lembek when handled. The skin on the outside is fried, which lends another dimension to the texture. Yes. I do eat fishcakes. I'm weird.

The "Pi√®ce de r√©sistance" would be the Oinky Lard pieces. Fresh, crispy and oh so ..... generous.

Don't bother coming on weekends though. Extremely crowded and might sell out earlier.

Visited this store as I saw some newspaper cuttings as well as certs plastered on the front.

ordered the rice, beef rendang and vege at the price of $5.

Verdict: didn't live up to expectations. You'd expect a dense and flavourful rendang but what I got was watery and flat. look at the photos and what I got and you'd see what I mean
After long walk to Upper Seletar Reservoir and beautiful sunset view, the delicious food in this restaurant is a special bonus.
üëç üëç üëç

Great ambience and impeccable service. Food is above average but not the type that makes you feel like you must come back again, especially because it is slightly pricey. Really enjoyed the wagyu don - the wagyu was super tender and the rice was well flavoured. Skewers and sushi weren't anything to shout about tbh. Loved the tartness of the cheesecake.
Food is nice. Friendly waitress..

(Translated by Google) Delicious food, friendly service

(Original)
È£üÁâ©ÂæàÁæéÂë≥ÔºåÊúçÂä°ÊÄÅÂ∫¶Âæà‰∫≤Âàá

Affordable, authentic and delicious Malay fares - just the way we like it. They have been there for a least 30 years.  Last ate there around 1990. And not disappointed on this visit.

Ordered Mee Soto on a Friday night.  Service was prompt and friendly.  Taste just right. And only $3.

Live Mandarin Getai was put bonus. Singing is ok la. Free entertainment

Was my first time there and I could instantly tell why it is a crowd favourite. The satti soru was HEAVENLY. Reminded me of a nice home cooked meal. We tried both the chicken and the prawn satti soru and both were delicious, but I preferred the prawn more.

The iced teh was sweet, but not to the point where it was overwhelming. I loved it nonetheless.

The staff will also give you a complimentary carrot halwa and even that was out of the world. And this is coming from someone who never really fancied halwa.

If not for the location, I would be their frequent customer, but I am definitely returning for more when I can.

Mee Rebus was sold out at 6:45pm!
We settled for the chicken satay and beehoon Soto drumstick.

The satay was awesome, tender and juicy.  The satay sauce enhanced the taste further.  It was rich and full of peanut crunch.

The beehoon soto was better than expected.

We would definitely go back to try the popular mee rebus.
Good loklok buffet, best for groups. Taste of Malaysia while we are stuck in Singapore

This Malaysian themed food court offered a wide variety of food. However, the quality was rather below average. The bak kut teh had quite a generous amount of ingredients for $5.50 but the meat was tougher than Mahathir and Lee Chong Wei combined, the soup lacked fragrance, the canned mushrooms were out of place and even the dark soya sauce with chilli was tasteless. The prawn crackers and prawn noodles were ok but far from great. The sugar cane was diluted. Seats were limited. Only cash was accepted. Also, the kitchen staff felt like they hated their jobs.

Small, cold and non crispy Fried chicken.

The star here is their curry sauce and Rice.
Surprisingly nice porridge with many variety and tasty.  Many nice side dishes.  But price slightly on the higher side.
Paradise for meat lovers. The waiting time may be very long and queue numbers usually run out by 7pm. But it is well worth the wait
Previously in AMK central s11. Now reopen here. I would say its the best chicken chop ever.  Great sauce and tender chicken. 6.50 and its worth it.
Highly recommend the 250grams NZ Ribeye. Ordered 2 times and each time was cooked perfectly. The side dishes are good too.

A little dirty but the food is hella good. The service is good too. Just the floor and tables looked oily. But I guess it's kinda normal? But anyway it's super good. Really recommend for eating at night. The atmosphere feels really warm.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Good Food.. Good Mood ü§ò

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: This stall‚Äôs carrot cake (white+spicy)‚Äôs great!! Not too dry/wet ü§§‚ù§Ô∏è

Gem in the west. Tucked inside kidstop and near science centre. One of the best Indian restaurants we ate at, value for money and good portions. They definitely deserve more ‚ù§Ô∏è. Make sure to ask for their recommendations if you can't take spicy food!

Always long queue but the serving speed is fast. Most of the dumplings are pre-made though as you can see the chefs keep making the dumpling behind the glass.

The queue management is ok. Just get the paper and wait for your queue. If you missed just tell and it will be your turn next. Most of the queues are about 30 minutes long at least.

Foods are good. There was one time I over-ordered a lot of dumplings because there are so many options. They were great until we were full. The truffles are a bit overpriced. One at $5.
100% muslim owned. affordable and sedap! The chicken teriyaki is a must try for u teriyaki lovers out there.
Cosy place . Good food . Will come back again . Nice experience

Genki sushi has always been my family's to go sushi place as my kids loved the sight of the train delivering the sushi. After visiting this place, I'm beginning to think that this may be our new hangout.

I really like the variety and uniqueness of the sushi they serve here. The especially like the thick cut salmon sashimi that is so satisfying to chew on. Food arrives promptly after ordering. Do come earlier as the queue forms rather quickly.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Chose the 2 pax set (actually can feed 3) which is what most people eat here. Priced at $53++. Honestly I‚Äôve had better jjampong and jajangmyeon noodles (more Q and softer) in other korean restaurants thus wouldnt come back for the noodles though we love the spicy jjampong soup and the generous ingredients given.

Their sweet and sour pork is however a good huge portion and served hot from the kitchen which makes it even more tantalizing. Their fried dumplings are also crunchy and delicious.

The sides are pretty minimal (guess you leave more stomach space for the mains) but the kimchi is good.

Pretty cosy and small space that is family run and service is great. Complimentary water is served as well.

Chicken skewer and grilled vegetables are packed with flavours while the beef is a bit hard / dry. All has a light charcoal flavour (which I like). You may want to order side dish as the portion is a bit small. No complaint here given a really affordable price tag.

Fish & Chips @ uno beef

sounds ironic? so yeah, ratings base on their fish & chips, have yet tried theur other dishes.... one can only eat so much at a time, a pity

their fish are those standard frozen sutchi fillets, quite well done and pretty tasty.

i suspect that the batter they used for their fish are likely to be the same used for their chicken wings and cutlet, not complaining as it taste kinda good

the coleslaw taste great, btw. can't say the same for the garlic bread which is definitely stale

would come back and try other items on their menu
Frieds were crispy.  Chicken crispy outside but inside was on the dry side.  Beef good quality.  Sides were good.  Ice lemon tea quite diluted.  Service is slow but friendly.  Price reasonable.

It was a great dinner evening today at TPY Safra and most of all they were so kind to call back my friend who make the reservation , to inform her that I have left my purse there after my dinner .
Ps. Thank you to Mr Wu üôèüèªto wait for me at the Safra lobby to hand me back the purse. Much appreciated with your kind gesture. üôèüèª
Pros:
Very clean place  - Spacious , great for wedding dinner , no cuts of plates and bowl and they were all squeaky clean! üëçüèª
Affordable buffet price with great taste !! Good quality amount of food for 2 person ‚úåüèª
Friendly reception & attentive service staff :)
Cons:
No credit card promotion . Only Safra member 10% discount

we have company dinner here,
i tried a lot of new food here.
the staffs were so kind.

We had the Penang laksa and Penang fried kway teow for mains and ngoh hiang for starter. The fried kway teow was moist and fragrant, but the laksa was average. Chendol was good, with generous gula melaka. Would come back again.
Not great. And it's more pricey then regular shops. $6.20 for coin prata. Normally we pay $4 max. Royal is also expensive. Taste is so so.

Recently booked a lunch slot a week before the date and the slot was confirmed. Nothing else was mentioned by the booking staff and the staff also did not mention there were 2 sittings.
Two days before the lunch, i was told that my slot for lunch as 11am to 1230.
I think this is very out of ordinary for a weekday lunch and I think it should have been told when the booking is confirmed, and not days before the lunch.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Nice and spacious, suitable for family.
Went with a toddler and the food was suited my toddler‚Äôs palate.

Good choices of variety of meat/ veg/ fish cakes/ mushroom.

Love the Thai soup base, had the sweet Basil chicken and Khao Soi as recommended by the staff, and it was really good.

Best service staff! Was attended by this staff Hock Seng, very attentive and he personally reccommend the soup bases to our family.

Would come back again.

Zichar stall staff's attitudes are pretty lacking. Food-wise is disappointing and standards dropping compared to last year. Hopefully they can improve n train their staff well instead of replacing them every 6 mths or so. Staff morale is low & most of them seem forced to work.

Wow, incredibly rude cashier guy at wanton mee stall. Quite uncough and not sure what's got into him to display such attitude to customers. Food wise, definitely not worth the time and money. Noodle is dry and way undercooked, very tough and has powdery feel to it. The char siew is dry and tasteless. The guy cooking it wore glove in 1 hand, and he picks up ingredients using the ungloved hand, which is kinda disgusting.

Remember visiting this place when I was young, recently visited it again and looks like it has had some modern revamp.

Food is consistently good and their usual specials like the Peking duck and popiah skin are a must order. We ordered some other items which were pretty good too.

Service was up to par and staff was on hand to attend almost immediately.
Nice food. Worth a visit

I seldom come across food this bad, but when I do, I feel responsible to the public to post this.

Service staff were impatient and inattentive from the start - rushed and missing orders, tea not refilled, internal conflict among staff

Food was bad and expensive for the portion sizes - vegetarian luo han was nothing more than a pile of canned mushrooms in oyster/soy sauce (?!!!), sheng jian bao skin was tough and doughy, wild steam shoots which was supposed to come with meat was a sad puddle of withered shoots in muddy gravy with not a single strand of meat in sight. The best part - they don‚Äôt serve rice or ginger (for their xiao long Bao). Which Chinese restaurant doesn‚Äôt serve rice??

This is a far cry from the 4.0 review that is stated on Google and other review platforms. Not sure if the owners/chefs had given up on life.

Please do NOT make a trip to this restaurant. Even if you‚Äôre in the area or happen to live around here, you‚Äôre better off eating instant noodles. An utter disgrace to Shanghai/Chinese cuisine üôÖ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

(NB - they should seriously consider redirecting their investment in the service robot to serving better food. Or at least try.)

It's okay, nothing too special about the porridge. No wok hei taste and one of my prawns was completely mushy, think their seafood is not very fresh.

Pretty generous with the ingredients though and the staff here are very enthusiastic and professional (esp the young boy who was attending to the tables)

It is in pioneer
Good place to eat
Very cheap price

Good to have for lunch & dinner
The plate bigger than the food. This one hawker or restaurant? $5 rather spend my money for donation. Scam üò°
Good food and a good service from Uncle Wilson. Thank you so much for the great service.

The waygu burger is nice. Thick juicy Patty on buttery bun
Fajitas is nice too. Lots of meat. Yum.
Molten lava lorte is a must have.
Apple crumble ok ok

New branding, new menu.
Grats on re opening.
Had 3 course set lunch 14 SGD nett. Most affordable from the menu already.
Mushroom soupü•∞ - creamy, heavy yet watery, truffle oil can't taste. Garlic butter bread was nice too.
Beef strip loinüôÇ - Doneness medium rare but come out medium. Lightly seasoned. Tasted okay. Chewy and tough. Paired with sauce or salt and pepper to enchance it.
Brownie üòã - Super moist, chocolatey and fudgy. Shiok. Must try.

Good ambient, place cooling, service indeed is great.
This their soft launch menu. So subject to change.

Perhaps the oldest restaurant still standing among all in the area. Sushi/sashimi platter was quite fresh. Worth giving it a try. Beef served in sizzling hot plate. Sake was given a decanter and chilled in bucket of ice.

A bit overrated and dry on few of the items, this Lok Lok seems to be deep fried only. Love the fried beancurd skin, mantou and the satay sauce.
There are also other choices like enoki mushroom with bacon, aubergine, cheese ball, broccoli, luncheon meat, quail eggs. Some of the food are really a bit dry and the foodcourt runs out of seats easily to mookata and the wait is long. I would come early if I‚Äôm coming second time.
My favourite place for hot & sour soup, beef noodle & fried rice.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Always a great deal and the food quality is consistent across the chain in Singapore.  What's even better is SAFRA members get a 7% discount at this outlet.  Sub SGD10 for a decent main (with the discount) is a good deal.
Very fast service with some interesting dishes. Closes a bit too early on a Saturday
had good food there so i will recommend this place

I was there with my family for the dinner ala carte buffet. The variety of dishes though not considered extensive, was pretty ok as the dishes were Chinese tzi char type and you won't aim to eat every single one üòÖ

I like it that the serving size is small, but just enough for the number of diners indicated. This allows us to order a particular dish again if we really like it and not to forcefully finish everything if it doesn't suit our taste buds. It also allows us to try out more of their dishes too without getting full just eating a couple.

There were a couple of dishes that I particularly like...eg fried hot fun and the fried fish. The rest were just very average and some coffee shop tzi char stalls have better to offer.

Service wise was slow, except for the first round of one time order dishes, the rest took a long time to be served and certain dishes were never served despite us having to keep checking with the serving staff. Most of the staff were friendly and responsive, with the exception of one who was pretty rude, and wasn't very willing to top up the tea or take any new orders, but was always busy walking around.

Though pricing wise, it may appear to be lower than many other restaurants serving buffets (note that tea and wet tissues are charged separately), overall I doubt I will be back in a long time as food is just average and nothing memorable.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Very worst food and bad service. Our family got cold in the same night after dinner. Restaurant is not clean. All uncooked, very cold, no salt, no spicy and unhealthy foods I ever had. Hackers center food is very far better than this restaurant.
Even we spoke to management as not satisfied.

Please all think twice before you go. It may good earlier but now it's very worst.

Decent portion for $5.50 basil pork rice with egg.

Saw others ordering garlic pork which looks good with the fried garlic bits too. May try it next time!

The portions were generous and the food is nice. The chili is absolutely tasty and goes so well with the rice. Personally, I prefer the sweeter curry as gravy over the rice. Only downside for me is the cracker is not as crunchy. Will definitely come back again.
Good Japanese food for a good price. Good for a casual lunch. Kinda tight packed seating. Self service but the staff is very friendly.
Prawn and pork rib noodles has the best pork ribs ever. Tender and juicy. I had the dry version and the chilli has a good kick. Most enjoyable bowl at only $4

Good place to eat. Reasonable prices with good mix of varieties of foods. There are ample
Tables and chair to dine in but expect pretty crowded during lunch and dinner time. Air conditioner very cold, Food portion are quite small but tasty enough. Overall good place to eat.
Nice side dish.
Love the buta don! Affordable and delicious. Wagyu don is not worth the price, beef was not tender.
Very good quality food cooked in traditional taste and decent service. Only downside is that food would be considered to be on the salty side, and price is on the pricey side

Soup Restaurant is one of our favourite places for family gathering. Along with the popular Samsui Ginger Chicken, soupy dish like the Baby Spinach with Century Egg, and the "wok-hei" Hometown Fried Fish Belly are our best-loved. Menu was designed to order the food in one glance and get it served quick. Very cheerful group of service crew. Like the traditional dining tables that come in different shapes and sizes. Special thanks to Jonathan for the birthday cake preparation and related services. Well done!
45 minutes still waiting for takeaway of 8 packets of briyani, not even crowded when we ordered.

Finally I decided to queue for this, pretty amazing as the queue is long but the system is good.  I got my food in a short time.  The friendly aunty that took the order is very organized.

I have ordered pok chops and chicken cutlet for my girl.  Well the pork chop meat is thin  but I felt is enough for us.

My girl said is delicious and couldn't finished hers.

For a 6 sgd chicken chop
And a 6.50 pork chop
Portion is decent huge.
Recommended.

Dinner ribeye steak was good.
The potatoes are the same as always.
Vegetables has improved though, tastes better now.

4 stars as the online ordering system doesn't seem to update the wait staff of the drinks, and the food came first. It was solve when we asked for our drinks.
Food is very nice and it's must to eat ultimate hawkerfest. Their customer service is excellent üëå
The food are getting more and more expensive. It cost $5.60 to dabao a packet of Hor Fun. Also the portion has become much smaller too.
Amazing food as always. The variety and quality of food never fails to amaze our family. Excellent customer service even during peak hours. Keep up the great work!

Nothing special in particular. The chawanmushi was served cold üò° and the green tea is powder form (hot water drips very slowly while you tries to fill your cup). Not recommended. That said, the claw machine to catch desserts for every $20 spent provides some family entertainment.

Generously huge serving portions, food tasted quite average, slow service as restaurant seemed under staffed. Service quality by staffs also sub par. Was given complimentary wings and a slice of cake without asking though.

Great western food in a cozy environment. We‚Äôve come here for the pizza as its hand made and fresh out from the oven. As well as the carbonara turkey bacon and the fish and chips, great choice and fulfilling too!
Come and check it out! ‚úåüèª

For its quality (very decent nasi lemak) and air-conditioned setting, the meal is fairly priced. And the folks serving behind the counter are friendly too! It is definitely worth a visit if you‚Äôre in the area.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Their martabak standard has gone down the drain. It used to be good and thick. Now not much difference from prata fold into two with little mince  mutton thrown in.

Wife went into the shop and told me to meet her there. I read the reviews here and told her not to order so much but she missed my message and ordered the fried rice with fried pork chop, xiao long bao, pan fried buns, gyoza, drunken chicken and barley. I had super low expectations but when the whole restaurant was seated, I wondered if the existing Google reviews were harsh. The fried rice was tasteless and the pork chop though nicely fried, was strangely sweet. The pan fried buns/gyoza/xlb all too, tasted weirdly sweet while the drunken chicken. The only thing that was supposed to be sweet - the barley drink, was tasteless. I've eaten local cuisine in Shanghai before and the food doesn't taste this way. Might be a failed attempt to localise the flavours. Wouldn't recommend.
Other than the long serving time, the food is wonderful here. I had chicken murtabak and my friend had an egg prata, they taste great, very savoury.

Ok this is the thing. When I ate at the restaurant years back, the curries were flavourful. I ordered delivery this time round, ordered a masala chicken, egg and kosong pratas.

Delivery was on time. The masala chicken curry was cold. It should have been at least warm. The taste, bland.

Hope they will make some changes and bring back the flavourful and savoury masala chicken curry.

Significant improvement on the food comparing to my first visit. Was thinking of holding more again but the service from the service crew greatly discourage me from going again. I do not understand why, is it because we did not order as per advise from the male captain? First Culinary, I supposed your response is highly appreciated. Hope to hear from you soon.
Visited multiple times since they opened. Friendly staff always.

Uncooked and dry rice. Not even sure if Japanese rice was used. Terrible pre cooked fried chicken which is cold. Beef has no sauce this dry . Please don‚Äôt waste your money. I want to put zero stars‚Ä¶ because was deceived my the Japanese chef‚Äôs poster so gave it a try.

The porridge is really good but it's over priced. The portions of the dishes, especially vegetables are really small. A plate of veg at about $8 is only enough of 1 person. So if you order a set meal say the grouper fish slice porridge with a bit of youtiao and a soya bean drink and you add a veg to it, it'll cost you around $22 without the ++.
Superb food as always. Pricey, yes. Value for money, not too sure. The fried rice is to die for as always. But a little ex for a small little plate.

@ Jasmine who wrote the review. Is not true. I have been there many times. If you cannot wait is not their fault. Looking at others assuming they waited long and not happy is your own judgement. $10 for a fried rice I would think is reasonable. Even a zhe char stall fried rice now is about $8. So I do not know what do you meant by expensive.

We can rate the food and service but should not judged what others are doing when we dont even know them..I dont see anything wrong with the lady boss going around greeting..this statement is a bit judgmental. Nothing wrong for her to go around even it is true. I think is not fair to judge just for a visit..think must be fair to rate the food but not judged people and put here online to embarrass her. She is just running a business..

The food here was great. Recommended many of my friends, they all love it. Waiting time was reasonable because of the crowd. We were patient and understand that the chef needs time to prepare and is worth waiting. Looking around, I could see there were many still waiting for their food. They all looked cool and enjoying their drinks. None of the customer showed any sign of impatient. Heard them thanking the lady boss for checking on them if they are being served..I could see there were many regular customers. Is a good sign. Good food is worth waiting. The price is reasonable. Will be back

It was located near Phoenix LRT, moved two months ago to Science center (rose from the ashes). Have eaten in or ordered out several times from the previous location and visited the new place, food and quality of service is still good.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Good, a bit spicy though.

This is my third time here and I feel like home always whenever I eat here. The owner is really such a pleasant person, and always serving such quality food with generous portions! The truffle beef don seals the deal for me, but the salmon üç£ is just as great. Hope this joint gets the recognition it deserves! üëçüëçüëç
Standards have way plunged down, doesnt taste the same, and the menu have changed. Food aint so fresh anymore. Having eating it for more than 10 years.

Went over to try during lunch time. Conveniently located, it is opp amk hub, and the way over is all fully sheltered.
Tried their ribeye steak and is very happy with it! The meat is really tender and was cooked to medium rare ask requested! The mushroom sauce goes perfectly well with it as well~ Love the fries as well! Dipping it in the baked beans sauce. The only item that was not up to par was the garlic bread. It doesn't have much garlic taste and it was rather sandy instead of crispy.
This is definitely a place that I will be going back to if I am around the area.
Recommend the preserved veg braised pork belly and yong tofu amongst the dishes I tried.

Went on a Saturday afternoon and it was very quiet, which we appreciated. We ordered the 6-pax course meal and really enjoyed the food. It was yummy, and the food was all served in a timely manner right after one another. Will definitely come back again soon!

Been dining at this place occasionally for a few years now, generally the food is good and service staffs are prompt. During birthday cake cutting, they will blast the happy birthday song loudly, quite old school but fun anyway. Price is reasonable too. Location might be bit hard to find for first timers thou.
So many ranges of good and tasty foods to select. Need to wait for at least 15-20mins. But it is worth waiting.
My wife is a Thai food lover. We tried a number of Thai restaurants before and this is one of her favourites. So it's good enough for me. And more importantly, it's affordable and nice.

Food is great, service used to also be good when they first opened, today was my visit after 6 months and I was disappointed.

Spoon provided was dirty, I asked for an exchange, the middle aged staff with dyed dark brown pony tail and hair bun attended to our table, no apologies provided. She took the list of order, which clearly stated 1 chicken rice, 1 plain rice, but served us 2 chicken rice instead. I highlighted, she did not even apologize and just exchanged with white rice.

We were preparing to leave and was about to wear our masks, halfway through she asked to clean the table. We kindly requested for her to wait till we stand up, she looked at her colleagues, repeated what we said while rolling her eyes. The reason we requested that was because we had past experiences where food and drinks were spilled onto our clothes during clearing, was it too much to ask since wearing mask was just 10-20 seconds?

Overall food was great, but fairly bad experience with this particular staff.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Simple place, food tasted better than expected. Staff who took my order was perplexed by my order, another staff suggested naan to go with the gravy I ordered. I'm on a low carb diet so no rice/bread. Appreciated the staff service and friendly boss. Craving for Indian food settled!

ordered food thru foodpanda.. sgd 15+ for thosa meal including delivery charge.. received food : only thosa + 1 idly!!!.. 1x vadai + 1x drink missing !!! and no notfication from komala's team.. contacted foodpanda team. very helpful. they manage the situation well.

Beautiful interior and very spacious, quiet on thurs evening. Food was veryyyy average. Melon tea by the pot, teabag type. Speculoos Cafe Latte was good because its totally not sweet at all though the name. Roffles Platter was very homemade... the roffles was not crispy and abit mushy. Sakura Cream Tagliatelle Pasta was below average, too much residue water from the seafood so the whole dish was very watery but the prawns were fresh. Seafood Aglio Olio was average. Fries with truffle & parmesan was good, very generous and huge serving, highly recommend. Visited this cafe to celebrate a friend's birthday so we also ordered a Lemon Meringue Tart which didnt taste fresh, below average.

Will recommend this place only for small bites and drinks. Good for a teatime break.
NICEEEEE ‚ù§Ô∏è Love the food here. Yummy. Will bring my family here to try.
Delicious! Black Bean Beef Hor Fun is a must try.

Very great experience. Food was delicious and worth it. Delightfully surprised that they use haddock (and not dory) for their fish and chips. Haddock has more flavor and has a firmer texture. Fries are thoroughly seasoned with spices and crispy. Even came with cheese and tartar sauce.

Duck confit was moist and just falls off the bone.

Would definitely return and I highly recommend the fish and chips.
We celebrated our 39th wedding anniversary in this restaurant and thoroughly enjoyed the delicious food especially the Beijing duck.
Lovely dishes with wide variety to choose from. Definitely affordable and vendors are extremely friendly!
We enjoyed the Olive Fried Rice, Steamed Lime Fish, Kailan with Pork, and Basil with Century Egg. Staff were friendly too!
Good food.
A rather interesting well decorated Chinese tea house, went there for dim sum lunch, good menu & food.
Literally living in this block, have been going to here almost every night for dinner. A29 Crispy Basil Chicken is just the PERFECT dish to go for üî•üíØ
One of the best nasi lemak that similar to Malaysian‚Äôs one! Generous portion, reasonable price and awesome customization available

This place has been around for quite a few years and it seems to still be going pretty strong!

Expect to find decent Japanese food with generous portions at reasonable prices. They are definitely more affordable in comparison to other more known brands in Singapore. Although their food is nothing extremely amazing, it's still a comfort go to place where you can go without feeling too much of a burn in your wallet.

Their set meals are especially worth the price, as you can great portions at extremely comfortable price range :)

Their staff was super friendly to us even though we arrived pretty near closing time. Kudos!!
Good quality Japanese food. Attentive service. I like it that there is a relatively high level of customisation allowed too.
Very nice kitchen facilities with chef and facilitators around for guidance always

Staff were very professional and service was top notch even if it's a more fast food style place. Love the fries, especially the chipotle seasoning and soft chicken taco :)) I don't normally eat tomatoes but it's really delish as they take out the tomato seeds and its so nice together as a whole taco
Surprisingly the stream fish was very nice. We never order chicken even they are famous for it. Just want to try other dishes
Food is pretty authentic. This is comment from my Shanghainess friend. Menu have limit dishes. Dish serve quite fast, their handmade noodle is a thumb up :)

Fuss free queue system, staff are efficient and helps to change the grill mat if needed. Many sauces to choose from and items are ready for collection very quickly after you order via the app. Overall it's one of my fave dining place.
first try

Ordered Gam Hiong Prawn Fried Rice via grab to Thomson medical centre yesterday.
Top with prawn paste chicken.
Both dishes were very fragrant and tasty!
Oh the chilli was awesome too. Surprisingly came with a coke.

Choose to try this because of the awesome review and replies from you guys. No regrets! Keep it up!

Side note, if the drink is part of the meal, can explore giving option to choose between a few drinks?

The branch at Compass One, food is average or below...I have visited 5 times before their renovation...food was tasty, non-oily and fresh back than...but today's visit was so terrible...noodles were too stiff too oily...sweet sour pork was too oily and the pineapple has already turn bad...it such a bad experience...I would not recommend anyone to visit...the standard of food handling, cooking and taste are kind of hopeless...

Completely Great Restaurant!!!!!!!
This one is full with singaporean and famous within local community.
No tourist at all.
Service is quite good. (Dont expect expensive restaurant type service here)

Ordered
1) Prawn Paste Fried Chicken (really goodddd)
2) MaPo Tofu (love it!!! Tofu also quite a lot and the taste is just perfectly balance. Not really spicy)
3) HongKong style steam fish (this one really good with very cheap price! Recommended!!!)
Love mapotofu here. One of the best dish
Hot and nice.  Back again here after several months.  Sushilicious is in Koufu food court at Toa Payoh Central.

Friendly staff, cozy atmosphere. Food is alright but perhaps we ordered the wrong dishes.
What we like:
Oyako don
Milk tea

Didnt like
Sushi coated with sesame and a frozen crab stick.
Sashimi was abit soggy and ika was terribly hard.

Almost two years since we last visited this place Service has dropped. Staff were rather unfriendly. Took super long time for the drinks (peach cooler, lychee cooler, longan coolers etc) to be served. Doesn‚Äôt make sense for simple drinks to take so long to be served. When it came, the peach cooler was very sweet. The aglio Olio was super super tough. Thankfully, the staff offered to do a replacement upon feedback.
Very good fried rice! Fav - Gam Hiong Prawn Fried Rice $8.90

This Aburi outlet is conveniently located at the ground floor of Jem. The outlet faces Westgate Mall and is located at the entrance facing Westgate. The menu consist of a selection of Japanese food bowls and raw fish. Tried a few of the Japanese rice bowls. The helping is sufficient but not excessive.

The lobster with steak were amazing. The Nepalese chicken has a special and unique taste on its own. The fries was really good. We went there on an eatigo app discount of 30%. Please remember to make reservations prior to arrival to enjoy the eatigo discount. It's a pretty neighbourhood and quiet place. The price is around $10 - 20 depends on the mains u ordered. But with the eatigo discount, we only paid 30 bucks for the amazing food that we ordered. Definitely will recommend this.
üëçüëçüëçüëç

I think this place deserves more credit. Everything that I ordered today was perfect. Service was a little sub-standard, but the food... I would come here just for the food. The Ê∞¥È§É was crunchy, light, the XO Carrot Cake flavorful, and the E-fu noodles just the right amount of oil.

Prime Karubi and Pork Belly were really good and able to select rice amount for big eaters. Price is reasonable and there are different sets available for selection, or you can order the meat a la carte. Layout of the place is ideal for people who are eating alone as well. Payment is fast with self payment kiosk as well. Long waiting time of about 70 minutes so be prepared to wait during peak meal times.

The server lady was rude and hesitant when asked of the pricing about food ordered. During payment, the lady insisted that 3 dishes was order instead of 2. Hence, charging more for 2 takeaway meals. The food is nice but with such dishonest business conduct, we never go there again.

Service was pleasant.   üëç
Had mutton bryani.
The mutton curry was nice...
Mutton too was soft but just not enough of the meat...guess it's at the tail end of the day.
No papadum with the meal üòî

Tea was on the thin side but drinkable.

Wang Thai Kitchen. Blk 92, TPY Lor 4. We came here 2 years ago in  2020. The food was very good and we eat there regularly. However when we ate there recently we were disappointed. The TH milk tea that we usually order tasted diluted. Our favorite garlic pork dish is no longer what it looks and taste. Now it looks like it is not well cooked. No more golden brown and crispness no more. Dont taste good. Dry chicken curry  standard has dropped a lot.  The creaminess and flavour is very flat. The uncle waiter used to be happy and friendly. Now he don't smile at all just Stern face all the time. We highly suspect they have changed the chef. It is just no longer the tasty food that we were used to having. I don't think we will ever come back here again.

Carried only a small selection of lok lok items, which are all simply deep fried. Then either sprinkled with a salt pepper mix or brushed over with a soya sauce based marinate. Everything starts to taste the same by your third skewer. Special chilli sauce packs quite a punch.

Ordinary. Even though at $1.

We didn't need to wait for a seat since we visited this outlet at about 3.45pm. I ordered the A5 Wagyu and US Karubi set with kimchi. Added up to about $23.50.

The Wagyu and karubi had nice marbling, and melts in your mouth. I like that the kimchi is sweet before the spice hits. Miso soup is alright.

Will visit again.

Dinner plans with a couple of friends, and decided to order from different places. So we ordered a Hana Bara (Mini) ($18.80 nett) as a takeaway order, and it took 15 minutes to prepare. Once done, brought over to another place just a couple of minutes away to dine in.

The block of brown in the middle was said to be a sponge cake, from another review, so when we tried...... We were confused, and couldn't really tell. 'Cause there were pieces of tamago with brown tops that looked like the middle piece, that tasted similar but not, you know? But not that big a deal.

Before I go any further, the main reason why this was a 1 star down was just because of the temperature of the sashimi. This is the first time that I have room temperature or un-cold sashimi don, which didn't quite sit well with me. I like my sashimi and sushi cold, you know? It's just the experience and expectation for Japanese cuisine.

Apart from that, everything else was awesome! The portion was huge, totally worth the $18.80, and not just the rice, but the sashimi and ingredients were plentiful! I love the mix of the furikake throughout the don, with the sashimi cubes and mixed into the rice. Everything was flavourful enough that I didn't need to mix the wasabi and soy sauce in.  Definitely can recommend to others!

service is good, Ubin Lala Bee Hoon very delicious and the price is $18 (take away $19),hot plate bbq sweet and spicy thai style sotong price is $22, claypot 3-cup wine chicken small portion is $15. Overall is good

If you're looking for authentic HK dim sum, Mouth Restaurant is the one to go for. My all time favourite and it's value for money too. Their cooked dishes are pretty good as well from the char siu to roast meat, wanton noodle and etc.
Wonderful service, nice dim sum and definitely great service!

my favourite lok lok stall in sg! im not sure if they bbq or deep fry, but it has more of a bbq grilled yummy taste and not oily. im guessing this could be a rare stall that do bbq over deepfry (most other loklok stalls deepfry)

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: More gravy, less meat, like soup but charged $9.90  at Jurong east venture ave. Too bad.

Zichar food that is reasonably priced. The cereal prawn and seafood noodles was good. Forget the coffee pork rib, the meat was tough and too chewy. Service is non-existent. Once they take yr order, it's hard to get their attention for service. The ambience is very casual.
Nice burrito bowl but wish there were more tomatoes.
One of my favourite late night supper place. Try their Crab Meat Pasta!
Wow!! good and nice food.So sedap not expensive 11am people to start Q.Must come early before 3pm all thier food will gone.Recommended Place!!!Thier Curry Chicken Must Try...

Glad to have found this Vegetarian Restaurant that is just 2 mrt stops from my place. Generally the food is quite nice and the minimalist decor of the restaurant makes U feel relaxed. Will visit again to try more dishes.
Good, affordable Hokkien style dishes. Had the red wine mee sua - perhaps one of the few stores in Singapore that does this dish properly.
The prize is reasonable

I'm surprised. Food is good. The duck, salted egg yoke prawn, yam dessert... all good. 6 x fresh steam scallop only $18.

I will return.

Lisa (staff) explained the details of the membership and she was so hospitable in serving us the food. My guests and I enjoyed our dining experience here.

I would definitely recommend friends to visit TungLok Teahouse.

I have eaten at this place since I was young, the green nasi lemak rice is fantastic, its so savoury that you can eat it on its' own, the prices are insanely cheap, at 50 for each item apart from chicken wings which is at 1 dollar. But there's a minimum expenditure of $3 per plate. Also note to be there early and expect a queue which however clear fast as they are really quick at service, they are usually sold out by 2pm everyday. Their curry puffs are a nice 50cent treat that will leave you wishing you have bought more for tea time in the office.
We made reservations. When we arrived, the waitress directed us to share a table w a stranger. Is that allowed? Perhaps the boss or even MOH should look into this.

Good selection of stalls from dessert, soup, rice and noodle dishes, rojak, popiah, etc.

Plenty of tables and quite clean.

Tried the popiah and it's alright, the green bean/sago soup and ice kachang are pretty good.

Great tasting ramen at coffeeshop price. Love the broth which is thick and yet not overly salty like most ramen soup. One of the better ramen stalls that is affordable and in a neighbourhood coffeeshop.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: This is a Hunan Cuisine restaurant. As you know about Hunan cuisine, the dish will be extremely spicy. Space arrangement is weird as it sits in one of the corner and not much room for large group gathering. I think this serves the basic need for you to try out a spicy Hunan cuisine.
Super yummy Indian food ! Best Prata other than Prata house . Super affordable üëçüèº Two pax - roughly $30 - their BEST butter chicken prata set, masala thosai, two teh iced

Love the food. Taste like home cooking which is always excellent. Very personable service too by friendly staff. Malaysian chefs and staff. I think I remember a famous food blogger says if all the Malaysian chefs go home, our zhi cha stalls will suffer. I believe so.
We had the claypot tofu which was full of roast pork and melt-in-the-mouth tofu and 3 cups chicken with a sauce that tastes like satay marinade. A tad too sweet for me. The hot Pulot Hitam dessert comes with a scoop of really frozen vanilla ice cream. Hubby really loves the combi. Will return again with other family members and friends.
Had their plain thosai and i like it!! Especially the coconut chutney and sambar, very flavourful. Coming back to try their pratas and other food items

Order their Teriyaki chicken set. Quite disappointed. The set don't even come with a bowl of miso soup.
Teriyaki sauce too sweet. Sliced cabbage potion is miserable.
Long queue, its because one man operation.
Overrated, not really worth it.

Excellent. Despite being a self-service establishment, staff are very attentive and helpful, with special mention going to the girl bringing us into the restaurant. Took the time to explain to us how to order and pay. As for the food, not much needs to be said about it; for the money, absolutely wonderful. This restaurant will be seeing more of this face very soon. Thumbs up!

(Translated by Google) The restaurant located at a corner location at balestier and you may not spot it immediately after few pass-by. Had a really great and authentic Chinese dinner for Dong Zhi festival with nice dumpling and sweet sour pork here.

Will definitely come back again!

Passed by numerous restaurants near my home, I decided to have a meal during the winter solstice. The portion of the Northeastern cuisine is really big and honest, and the taste is very homely and authentic. Baobao meat is the most delicious thing I have ever eaten!

The proprietress is so kind and very nice, and eating at the winter solstice really brings warmth to the wanderers in Greater China. I hope the business of the boss and wife is prosperous!

(Original)
The restaurant located at a corner location at balestier and you may not spot it immediately after few pass-by. Had a really great and authentic Chinese dinner for Dong Zhi festival with nice dumpling and sweet sour pork here.

Will definitely come back again!
