Always love their dang gui  ya

Had the premium set for 2 for lunch. Food was amazing, with the signature crispy papaya salad as the greatest highlight for lunch! Will definitely come back and try their crispy papaya salad with soft shell crab. Amazing service as well, as our needs/well-being/quality of food was checked on by the service crew.
The service was excellent. We were hosted by Ivan who check in regularly with us to see if the food is alright. The dishes we order taste great and the ambience were nice.

2nd time visiting this shop after being taken over by Srisun. Previously the service was superb . The people take so Long to initiate order from customers eventhough not many customers around. Left without ordering . This is the worst shop ever!

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: One of the best authentic Indian restaurant in AMK. Served a wide range of dishes and options. Try the Uthappam. It‚Äôs good. My regular local india place to enjoy good food without having to go little india üëç
Decent restaurant for western food. We like their fish & chips and lobster bisque soup. This store also has an Udders ice-cream store inside. Usually not crowded and located next to Toa Payoh MRT.
Came with a 10-month old baby, the staff was able to give us a corner table and baby chair. Food was hot and nice portion. Staff was friendly too.

Nice and gd.

But the nasi wet wet one. So when you buy, eat fast later spoilt liao

Update 18 October 2021:

Long queue when I come 830. Anxious scared chicken finish. $3 where to get Nasi lomak with chicken, egg, ikan bilis and fish.

Many smelly cheapo singapore talk so much. Say Food not nice la, chicken black la. Come on its $3, budget lomak with all inside. Where to get?!!

Not happy to eat, go eat yr atas Nasi lomak. Later complaint atas lomak expensive la.

Relax la why so angry. Spore already so stress. Food also want to be angry when u pay $3 only.

Ordered grilled pork chop and chicken chop with spaghetti. The pork chop was one of the better one I had tried as most of the time pork chop tends to be tough. The sides were nice especially the curly fries, they were hot and crispy. The chicken chop was good too though the spaghetti was more average (a lighter version). I will definitely visit again.
Best Food & Best People! AWESOME

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Ordered the Roasted Duck Drumstick Rice through GrabFood, since it was stated "top-rated". While some parts of the meat look like drumstick, the others look like other parts of the duck. Besides there were plenty of bones, the meat was tough like chewing on rubber. The gravy was a bit too sweet. That was the first time I tried. It will be the last time I ordered anything from them as well.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: 100% vegetarian food . Great place for a good vegetarian food. serving south indian and north indian items. Had delicious food.Very friendly staff.

Went there 2 weeks ago and promised a review for the amazing service that i've received from Joan.

She has been attentive to all the needs of the consumers, and i'm using this opportunity to thank her for the good service.

Food is good as well, you'll need to book in advance to prevent waiting.
The fishhead steamboat is famous and must try, rest maybe hits n misses, according to my accompanying diners

Generally good food quality. The affogato is served with strawberry vanilla, my wife didn't like it but I'm fine. Good price value for neighborhood location. The truffle pork chop is genuinely grilled to excellent flavour and tenderness.
Extremely rude staff who are very inpatient at customer, waited for a good 2 minute at the cashier only to receive a lashing by them asking me to wait when i tried to order

Officially a fan of this place! 2nd time here and very impressed by the authentic flavours of the Thai food! One of the owners,Uncle Vincent, was really accommodating and friendly and takes the time to answer our questions and talk to us and check if everything is ok, even though the restaurant was pretty busy! Will definitely patronise again!
Best vegetarian restaurant in this area

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Basil Pork would have taste better if freahly cooked.

Nice environment.
Mini ballroom feel
I'm here attending CNY dinner.
Friendly stall owner..

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Sooo good well worth the trip after a hefty hike at macritchie! We had prawn noodle yum yum!

Authentic Hakka restaurant located at Upper Thomson area. Serves Hakka dishes such as yam abacus ÁÆóÁõòÂ≠ê, salted chicken, yong tau foo and Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ„ÄÇDecoration is very 70's style and bring back memories from that era. Worth the trip up north if you are craving for Hakka food.

WoW. Is it possible that every dish you order is worth your 4 or 5 star rating without complains?

That is what happened to my family and I last week. Food ordered were roast duck (yummy), braised beef (with tendon in clay-pot), spinach (wet with egg), chee chung fun (crispy mushroom), pear and ribs soup (double boiled), 3 treasures porridge(smooth).

Staff were attentive and courteous even though placed was PACKED. The queue outside was insane. Quality food and family time spent =)
China lady dont care about customer's question. When asked if there is non sugar soy milk. Ignore customer and attend to another person who jump the queue somemore.

Visited this original outlet for the first time with my partner. Pleasantly surprised by the selection available, especially the yearly favourites. Service was pretty fast too.

We ordered a beehoon goreng, mozzarella cheese prata, plaster blaster and D√§s Pr√§tw√ºrst with 2 teh tarik. OMG everything here was super tasty. Crispy prata with nice ratio of cheese to prata. The plaster had good eggs Benedict too and the sausage prata was a nice twist to currywurst!!

The beehoon was also moist with nice sized chicken bits and egg (meat and egg are add-on charge). Very pleasant meal. The curry for the prata was also rich, right spiciness and flavourful. Made all the prata stood out too!

Will be back for other pratas they have!!

It‚Äôs a decent place. Love the signature Cheong fun, crispy and succulent shrimps. The durian glutinous dessert is okay.
Fully automated using conveyance belt to deliver to you.
Nice ambience n nice food

Had a feast for lunch.
Good standard for the various dishes.
Great customer service as well

Our family go to place. Great A5 wagyu steak and the fried rice, on top of our usual order of kawa. Next time , I would like to try A5 wagyu shabu shabu or sukiyaki with our usual with the sake..Look forward to this.....
Great murtabak,rojak,bonesteak and other indian food. Not to forget their teh tarik....is to die for.
Very bad experience for the rude attitude of the cashier, never come again!!!

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
O.m.g. very good.

The Gobi Manchurian was rich and flavorful.
The Fish Tikka was tender and juicy.
The butter chicken set was nice and well-balanced too.
Masala tea could be better though.

Sorry didn't take any photos.. We cleared everything on the unassuming plates before I thought of that. Lol

My gf had Gam Hiong Fried Rice and she felt it's 5 stars for the flavor, I had Venison Fried Rice and it would be 5 if not for the slightly overpowering ginger taste... Pork chop was well tenderised but not enough to wow in terms of taste, still need to work on the marinating sauce combo... Overall above average and will be back!

Yummy and tasty dun chicken and mutton briyani.Generous serving and quick service.Reaaonable pricing too...We ordered Vasai for teatimecascwell and it was still warm when delivered. Will definitely recommend to everyone.
usual place for breakfast on a weekend for me. usually good but this morning - jun 2019 was not good. prata served cold. no sambal chilli.
Like the fish curry gravy. It's taste great with the roti prata.

A small unassuming gem of a restaurant quietly hidden in the depths of Ang Mo Kio.

It was a very simple menu, every item was decently priced, and they arrived each was carefully made.

Drunken chicken was delicious. Other yummy things included the pan fried meat dumplings, pumpkin dumplings and Xiao long bao.

Highly recommended.

It‚Äôs a small place so book before you go.

Try the penang prawn mee, the soup too salty. The lean meat a bit hard due to boil and place for long time. The lean meat should only cook when order to keep it soft and tender.Salt should reduce in making the soup. Prawn quite fresh.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Nice food ..Yummy... especially enjoyed the chili üòã
Ordered the wagyu flank for $17. Portion and taste  mediocre. Sweet potato tempura was poor. Potato salad was ok. Not worth the money or time.

The selection and quality of this place is decent. But the service is horrendous. They sell a variety of beers but the drink stall helper has no idea what the beers are and blames it on the customer that they should communicate in Mandarin whereas all the menu items are in English. Even when taking orders for coffee and tea, the person in charge could not apprehend just 2 simple orders. It is okay to have the lack of knowledge, but the attitude to put her lack of on the customer is unacceptable.

Ordered Salted Egg chicken cutlet.

Full of flour and the Salted Egg sauce is so watery and bland.

Do not come and try.

Tried their medium rare beef sirloin steak, is only $11.9, considered as one of the best western stall(kopitiam) in AMK area.

Their chicken steak/pork steak costs only $6.9, and they serve super generous portion!
We mainly ordered mutton biryani. The mutton wasn‚Äôt that tasty. My first time here so couldn‚Äôt compare and say whether standard has changed. It was just average.

Compared to other Chinese restaurants (eg: Tunglok, Peach Garden), I would say this restaurant beats them all in terms of the quality of the food served and service provided. My whole family enjoyed our dinner buffet where we were impressed with most of the dishes and left with a full and happy stomach.üòã

All sorts of Japanese food in one area! The Sushi Go train is fun! Have your sushi delivered via a mini train rather than on the usual conveyer belt. There's also ramen, yakitori, bakery, dessert, just to name a few. Bring your $ and empty tummy.

Disappointing as we went based on the good review. Flavors of the food was tasting washed out‚Ä¶we ordered garlic chicken which was the worst as it tasted like chicken had been refried. Food was on the oily side. Fried chicken wings tasted like the pre packed frozen chicken, not the authentic Thai flavour.

Cheated by them! Ordered salmon belly but got normal salmon - for such a price $21.80 i think theres all grounds for a complaint here so others will know. Ur not a top end restaurant so the basic thing u shd be aware of n respect is trust and integrity and im sorry u failed miserably - and if u cannot uphold this then u shouldnt even be a business entity

We were early 1105am so decided to wait for the restaurant as there were seats outside. 1 of the lady service crew came over as she was on her way out to the ladies toilet and ask in Chinese why are you here for? ‰Ω†‰ª¨Êù•ÂÅö‰ªÄ‰πàÔºüObviously waiting for your restaurant to operate as you open at 1130am to have a meal on ‰∫∫Êõ∞. 2 of my aunties were already saying then we come here for what if it‚Äôs not for lunch. üôÑ anyway the staff just casually replies by saying ‚Äúyou all know we operate at 1130am‚Äù we nodded. Hmmm‚Ä¶. I think she can put it in a nicer way lor. Anyway we order the set meal and food was acceptable. Btw, my 2 aunties are regulars at this branch as they pointed which staff recommended which dish and they both love it on their previous visit.

Awesome HK style restaurant! Casual and relaxed atmosphere. Service is decent and not overly tight like most restaurants.

Food is very good. Not overly heavy on seasoning as most places and has a very clean taste to let the ingredients speak. Think home cooking with no msg or added salt/sugar...

Har Cheong Gai was perfect! But skip the chili sauce that came with it doesn‚Äôt enhance the dish.

Coffee pork ribs was amazing! Fall of the bone while good crisp outside.

Choy poh home made tofu was yums! The nicely crispy choy poh bits gave great saltiness enhance you rice or noodles to go with the meal.

Samba sweet potato leaves great balance of sambal flavor but not overpowering.

Sam lo hor fun was very ‚Äúclean‚Äù and not overly season. Subtly dish to let the fish and wok hei of noodles shine.

Highly recommended and definitely back again soon!

@iambruisedlee
Another Tori Q. Low price Japanese grilled food.
Nice prawn broth and lor mee. Boss gets frustrated when business is good. Don't expect service ok. Order, eat and go.

I love the diced chicken and Omelette.
Good for group lunch to share many dishes.
Another delicious Indian Muslim foods restaurant. Just only seating capacity limited to 30 to 40 pax only. Parking space No problem

Their Asam Fish head is awesome .
Staff is very good and polite.
Worth it to pay a visit .
Great seafood, and local cuisine.  I'm told it's some if the best in Singapore, and hard to get into without a reservation.

Nice cosy joint for authentic Thai food. Will overall recommend with below dishes tried:

-Crisy garlic fried pork belly : really good recommendation by the staff. This is not on the menu but has fantastic flavours. Wasn‚Äôt overly fatty as well.

-steam seabass with spicy sour soup

- Chili Kang Kong is pretty standard.

Visited the amk hub branch for lunch at 1140am. Waiting time 20min for 2 ppl still reasonable. But food tasted a little meh. The rice didnt taste like japanese rice, not enough vinegar. The sushi that tasted best were those with lots of mentaiko sauce, enough to overpower the rice taste. Tea is powder instant tea which is also a little meh..

I don‚Äôt understand why so many people giving positive comments on their prawn mee! I went to try for the 1st time after reading those positive reviews, sadly to say it is overrated, soup is too oily and lack of prawn taste! Will never buy again! The best Penang prawn mee I ever tried so far is located at amk hub malaysia boleh!
Food was tasty. Ambience was good. And service staff were friendly and helpful.
Generous portion and value for money western food. Definitely worth coming back for different dish as their menu has a variety of selections

Good quality NZ ribeye steak at good price!
Appreciated the thoughtful service when the chef re-plated a half eaten steak when we needed the raw parts more seared.  Good service üëç
The fish head curry is good. But the price point is higher than normal Zi char. Very surprised that the food taste very good

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: I like to go there. Wet market, level 2 hawker stalls. Today I was there for breakfast, and did my marketing. At level 2 the wanton noodle stall still has long Q, I missed it because I do not want to Q. I found Â§©Â§©Êù•Hokkien fries noodle. I was very delighted. Unfortunately I did not get to eat. I will be back again to eat Â§©Â§©Êù•Hokkien Noodleü•∞ a must to eat food.

Dimsum full of filling, crunchy. Prawns fresh. Steamed pork rib tender n marinated well. Only let down was char siew, nothing special.

Overall good chinese food, slightly on the pricy side.

This gyuu don (on that day) surprised me! Wow! The texture of the beef well grilled and tender..
Will be back to try others food again.

Canton Paradise CompassOne has had a major redecoration and it looks great.
As usual, the food was great and the service staff was attentive and helpful.
Always a good place for a tasty meal.

I liked the flavorful curry ramen, which has a really big portion that can feed 2 if you order one more side dish (if you are not a big eater). Gyoza has quite flavourful fillings and a just nice charred aroma. Service was quick and friendly and there was no big weekday lunch crowd. One star deducted for the fly that keeps disturbing me during my meal though, which is generally an issue for all the open air restaurants in JP basement.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Great place to gather for dinner and some drinks. The white and brown fried rice was surprisingly good. The black tofu and London duck were average. Try the satay (not on menu); every stick was generous with meat and had a good bite to it.
Need to improve  the service

There was promotion for lunch , would say that was not as expected as it is talk about.
Salmon with spegathi was just ok ..my friends steak was soso only.
Great food and service. Every dish was excellent in taste and presentation. A great place to bring visitors to Singapore to try the best of modern Chinese cuisine.
Quiet dining experience. Food was served quickly, however the drinks did not come with straws and have to request to be given.

An excellent place to host farewell.  5 of us visited the restaurant at Windstedt. Was impressed with the service by a serve staff Siti. Very warm and bubbly personality. Good in recommending thecashtypes of menu to choose both for main and desserts.  Malayan Council must be blessed to have her as server . Credit shod go to the cashier fir her waym personality.  Overall we had a great time there. We will definitely patronise the restaurant again. Thanks to them and the wide range of fusion food served

Great value for the amazing food they serve. The portions are big (there were two rows of pork in my pork belly don!) and they taste really good. Definitely a place for a nice grill meat meal.

The pork belly don and salmon don comes with kimchi and half a soft boiled egg, while the steak don comes with an onsen egg.

Hidden gem among the industrial area. Parking is easy. Ordered beef brisket (with mash potato), pork belly (with garlic fries) and mad spice chicken (with ratatouille). Pork was well done, no gamey smell, flavor was just right. Beef  brisket was well seasoned but I feel it‚Äôs abit too dry. Chicken had the strongest flavor, charred with crispy skin. Perhaps some of the charred can be removed first because it tasted bitter. Price was very reasonable. Worth a try.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Delicious jjajang and jjampong. Everything was so good that we ordered another set for second round ü§©
Recommend to make reservations before heading down to avoid waiting.

Can‚Äôt wait to be back the next time!!! ü§§

slow service, told us 15 mins wait but ended waiting 45 mins for just 3 dishes. kankong was ok, white beehoon was bland. we came here to eat the baby squid which we had before, but sadly the standard dropped, small portion and relatively hard to chew. smoking area in coffee shop made the wait v unpleasant.

Had the dim sum lunch buffet today. There were many misses amongst the dishes we ordered.

Pork ribs tasted stale and dry. Very much like they were overcooked and left out for awhile. I need my pork to tear from the bone, soft, succulent and juicy. This was none of that üò£

Pomelo mango sago tasted too much of the packaged mango pudding üò£

Posh interior design and TOP-notch service by the crew today offered some redemption. Very attentive service üëçüèΩ lovely place.

We made appointment for the 2nd-seating at 1.15pm. When we arrived at 1.15pm, we were told to ‚Äúwait on the couch bcos the previous party has not left yet‚Äù. There was a time limit to our meal, last order 2.30pm. Not a first good impression. We made the effort to be punctual, could there be a better way to manage the previous patrons from the first seating? Something for the restaurant management to think about. The wait staff‚Äôs communication was that they were really helpless.

We also asked for a high chair during reservation but were told to wait, bcos ‚Äúprevious patron was hogging the high chair‚Äù. It honestly disappointed me when this mismanagement of the restaurant became a problem cascaded down to me- also a customer of the restaurant. When we left the establishment at 3.15pm, high chair was still not received.

Called to make booking and was told will be given birthday boy/girl for free if we meet the number if pax. Upon arrived, can‚Äôt find my booking record, and charges are also different as communicated over the phone. Suggest to take down the person name if you make phone reservations. The china lady who handle us at counter and payment was not friendly honestly. The food & service acceptable except the admin part.
Small eatery on the second level of Tai Seng Centre. Loved their truffle beef rice bowl. Comes with soup and side salad. Great place for lunch but can get get filled quick by the office lunch crowd.

A simple yet delicious get together dinner with my cousins.
Service staff were polite and helpful. We were shown to our seats promptly upon checking in, and they even helped to change our utensils when we change over for dessert.
The new QR ordering is easy to use and our orders came in promptly.
The automated delivery train is fun and easy to use, thanks to the clear direction indicated.
The highlight is definitely the sweet and sour meat which came in with a grand appearance thanks to the dry ice effects.

Da bao 3 packets of char siew rice this evening and was surprised I was charged $16.50! There was no price list.

The portion is normal, packaging is normal using paper wrap, and while it tastes alright, it does not justify that exorbitant price when I can get similar quality elsewhere for abt the half the price.

Over priced, would not recommend.

1. High prize for common street food
2. Good qualities for stuff eating
3. Quite greesy
4. The lemonade (orange something) not that tasty but nothing to pick atleast better than water of chrysanthemum

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: It was really value for money. For $22 a set for 2, you get 2 medium size prawns, some squid, pork belly, chicken, pork, 4 scallops, enoki mushrooms, cabbages, xiao bai chai, corn, wong pok and an egg. We did not order rice or noodles because the amount is perfect. The thai dip is superb and spicy too. Our first time there but definitely will make many return trips there. We call in advance but was told no more reservations were alot. Staff told us we can do a walk in. We went there at 9.45pm and got a table immediately. Best to avoid dinner time. Last order is at 11.30pm.

I really love the Wagyu Steak and Prime Karubi. The price is so reasonable and worth the money.
Great atmosphere as well as the staffs are all very friendly and attentive and you can feel the positive vibes they have.
Nan basket with chicken gravy superb. Tandoori chicken was juicy and spicy.

Normally I m not a fan of vegan food but lotus made me craving for vegetarian food. It‚Äôs more like Chinese fusion style and all of them are tasty and flavorful. I would make my effort to come for great veggie food.

Happened to walk pass  this small cosy Japanese  casual restaurant.  Decided  to have my lunch with my wife.  Food exceeded my expectation.  The waiting  time  a bit long, seem short handed.
Well,I have a amazing lunch. I be back  to visit  again.

3/6/22
Crispy! Reasonable Price!

Ordered Egg Prata, Coin Prata, Ghee Thosai , & Butter Chicken.
But wish that the Coin Prata can crispier.
The Thosai sauces so so only, neighborhood taste compared to Little India.
hands down best place for dumplings. Not to mention their egg fried rice which is amazingly delicious and value for money !
Used entertainer 1 for 1 bento/ramen. Very mediocre food. Ramen taste like Maggie mee, egg is hard boiled egg. Salmon sashimi was thinly sliced.

Authentic Malaysia style fishball noodle. Another hidden gems in SG.
By the way, be prepare long queue and usually 11am already sold out.
I had a great chicken branyi menal here. The current is thick and pretty tasty:) papadam freshly fried and crispy.
Great service, sushi is fresh. Menu options are good. My frequent haunt.
Delicious, just that the spiciness is greatly reduced to suit to the local customers.
Good.

The food is a little bit pricy but acceptable. Don't recommend order ËÄÅÂåó‰∫¨ÁæäËùéÂ≠ê as the portion is quite small.
As for the taste, it is good.
The most upset thing happened was the table next to us was realy loud. other customers also asked them to keep voice low but no use. So it was horrible experience in terms of the environment. However I'm sure this is an occasional case.
Beef Rendang is extremely tender! Pekedel is cripsy on the outside and fluffy inside.

Good curry. And good variety of South Indian / Malay food. Normal service as seen in other Singapore curry houses which means nothing to compliment about but is ok if you are there only for your curry fix!
Unable to choose portion size. Its a buffet but portion size is fixed by number of pax. Some of the food taste stale. Not worth the price and poor experience

Place order using online menu QR. fast service. Some items on physical menu may not be available on the online order because physical menu is less updated. Have to separately order fresh coconut in person but service staff is helpful & prompt. Found lemongrass tea quite seeet even though there was option for less sweet, less ice. Tomato snapper fish (no picture) was good.

Had an amazing team dinner here. Top notch food and great value for the quality. Every dish was meticulously prepared and presented. The service was just as good if not better. Special mention to Nareenth who took care of our group. He was always there but never intrusive - that is top class service. Will definitely be back.

Walking 2 rounds in Mayflower Foods Centre but many stalls were not open this morning.  So went to the nearby coffeeshop for the Malaysian-style fishballs noodle.  I had my dry mee kia with ‚Äò‰∏ÄËâ≤‚Äô yellowtail fishballs only ($5.50) and a piece of fish cake ($2.50).
The sauce mixture was slightly saltier but savoury & did not have any hint of vinegar in it.  "Also no black sauce for me!"
It was served with plentiful of fried shallot, chopped green spring onion & pork lards.  The belacan chilli paste was not very spicy but flavourful enough.
The mee kia was quite similar to the instant noodle and pleasant to the bite.  It has seaweed in the soup which made it very tasty.  I opted for fishballs only because I don‚Äôt like Tou pok. üëçüëç

Located in the North Wing of North Point Shopping Centre.
The service was good and attentive. The staffs would ensure the water was filled up, the food was served fast, emptied dishes were cleared fast. Didn‚Äôt expect that Putien service standard to be so high.
The dishes were good. The lor mee was fantastic, both the traditional (white colour) and the listed type on the menu (red colour) were very good. The clams cooked with salt were nice. Enjoyed the food very much.
Another great experience with Putien.
Excellent place to have a great meal.

Tried the glass noodles, mango salad, stir fried kang kong & clear tom yum soup with prawns. All was wonderfully cooked except the soup was not really to my liking as compared to Soi Thai. Price was reasonable and serving portions were generous.
Rice is hard. Fried chicken got smell. Otah and egg is edible.

Do not order the Orh Ni (Yam paste coconut dessert) . The one we ordered was sour. Upon checking with the staff, they admit the ingredients were from nights before and prepared a new bowl. The chef even came out to stare at us angrily for no good reason. The new bowl have a stale vegetable oil smell. The rest of the dishes were ok and their service was mediocre. It was not priced to their standards. At the same price range we could've gone peach garden and avoided all this. They used to be good not now. Not that great.

Mee Rebus was the best I have eaten for a long long time. Definitely worth the money paid and effort going there.
Returned to stall this evening at 6.35 pm since it is listed as closed at 7 pm.
Unfortunately the stall was already washing up.
Next trip will have my family go along to try the Mee Soto (reported to be just as good) as well.

Fun time with girlfriends! Cooking is fun when the dirty dishes disappear as you put them in the sink!  Chef Elsie was very patient in explaining the steps and gave us tips on how to make full use of the ingredients. Thanks for the fun experience!

I patronised the branch at casuarina road. Called one day before to inform them I will pick up the order at 11.15am. Reached the shop at 11.04am to settle payment and collected my order at 11.32am. unpleasant experience. If you can't honoured the time, then let me know when I put in my order and not having your customer to wait for God long how long! I need to rush off to other place fyi. I have to rush them to speed up because I have other appointment to attend to!

Excellent Service by Daphane. Everyone loved the Peking Irish Duck which was served 4 ways, especially the skin with the popping candy. Fish was very fresh and the Salted Egg Cereal Prawn was done very well   It was my mum 70th birthday celebration and Daphane placed the free longevity buns around the cake that we bought creating a very appetising.

Booking is required to secure a table on 1st and 15th days of lunar month.

Food is very good, taste and quality wise. Sambal petai is very spicy but delish.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: The food was excellent! Impressively done by the chef, and as far as Chinese food goes, especially during crowded festive season, they sure maintain a high standard.

Good congee specialist in the Novena area. Wide selection with some dim sum and side dish options. Congee is smooth and quite flavourful. Could do with more 'wok hei' for greater impact. Nonetheless, one of the better ones around.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Suki Hotpot had reasonable variety and quite authentic. Atmosphere was great with attentive staff, especially Shidah, who made us feel very warm, welcomed and very attentive to us. üòÅ

Small little restaurant in Ang Mo Kio which has been around for Many years. Home cooked styled Shanghainese food. Simple yet authentic taste. Owners are from
Shanghai who has settled in Singapore for many years. High standard food with reasonable price. Totally worth a try !
Came on a raining day and queue was short. Delicious! The DaoPok was especially good! Super friendly store owner.
Of the four Thai food stalls in the area, this one is the best and most affordable.
Very soothing for stomach and price is reasonable.
nice environment and had fun time. love it

A really spacious cafe newly opened just months ago. Comfortable and cosy seating.. serving great pasta towards the Asian texture. Love‚ù§Ô∏è the small portions available for the small eatersü•∞ #msgreedysis #greedybuddiez

Been passing by this restaurant for many times but never stepped into it.
Today's my 1st and definitely will not be my last.
Authentic tasty homely Japanese food. Ordered a salmon bento + grilled squid + udon.
The food isn't salty. We love the grilled squid. It is soooooo good. Highly recommended dish.
The portion of bento and udon is satisfying.

Didn‚Äôt order the beef. The pork too tasteless and hard. Fish abit soggy not crispy. Chicken chop still ok. Overall will not come back here again. Tried their food 3yrs ago and I rem it‚Äôs much nicer. So I would say their standard has dropped quite abit.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Food is authentic Indian food. Had dum biryani, butter paneer, egg dosai and tissue prata. Price is reasonable.  Prefer this 10x over places like Springleaf prata place.

Update:
Inflation is bad. The serving size is quite small. Lucky to have 5 small cubes of meat in their mutton.
Waiting time is very long... order 2 egg prata and you have to be prepare to wait for 30 mins or more...

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
About 11 minutes walk from Caldecott MRT.
Not the busiest hawker centre but with the usual food and items you are looking for.
Surprising nice food at neighbourhood. So far all the dishes I tried are nice. Bring your own catch fish to them for cooking in your preferred method for $15
Good service, Good food, value for money meal.
Great food and ambience. The egg Benedict prata not only looks delicious, the taste is indeed superb. Really enjoyed my teabreak.
Nice halal food. Always come here for the chicken rice
Worth for money to pay for and meet my expectations
I've the mushroom puff

Dropped by for dinner without reservation on Saturday night. Had to wait a bit for seats. Ordered Tamako Teishoku (beef yakiniku) using phone via a QR receipt they provided. Food took quite awhile to come but understandable as the restaurant was packed and there was takeaway orders too. Teishoku set is value for money as it comes with rice, miso soup, ebi fry (prawn tempura), nikujaga (potato with meat), deep fried dumpling, chicken karage (fried chicken) and beef yakiniku. Every item is hot and freshly made. Beef yakiniku is on the salty side but rice complement well with it. Overall had an enjoyable meal!

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Average and not worth the queue and your calories. All the dim sum just too salty and the porridge is tasteless.

Go try next door fishball noodle as it seems taste better.

I liked the food and decoration, but service was not ideal. No one welcomed us after we sat and we had to wait for the menu. Although Waiters and Waitresses were walking around. Our dishes were not served together.
Always missed the food here, love the taste and favour. There is a 1 for 1 on weekday from 2.30 to 5.30pm . Quite worth it

Haven't had it for sometime now but the chicken rice, chicken, the fragrant soya sauce and chili plus the crispy tofu. Would like to add that the only missing item would be to have some nice hot soup served with the meal to make it even better
Nice western food and options

(Translated by Google) I write Chinese because I want my boss to see it. It used to be really delicious, although the price was more expensive than other places. But after this time, I will never consume it again. I take out medium spicy food, but it is not the taste and spiciness I have eaten all the way. Tonight I ate exactly like a super spicy chili boiled dish, not fried. The taste, and too much chili pepper and chili oil. Really can't eat, can't maintain the standard, customers can't keep

First visit and already feeling good vibes about the place. I didn't try the prata yet. But epok epok and vadai both are great. Will update my review the next time I try prata and the rice/noodle dishes. :)
Very delicious would recomend people to eat

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Good taste! Very convenient for the whole family too. Will definitely buy again!
Good food at great prices, the chicken thigh don is really nice - especially the leek. The gyudon is decent enough, but kind of tough. Their more premium beef options fare better.
Outlet has more varied selection of fried beehoon and noodles. It provides seating area too. Makes a lovely pit-stop before continuing with rest of journey.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
I had difficulty logging in to my Safra App however the waiter still provided me the discount.

Food portion was good and taste ok.

Newly renovated and it is brighter now.

Air conditioning was a bit cold for me though.

Overall was a good experience.

The place is at the Boon Lay Int. The food here is really tasty, good quality and hygienic.
The staff is very kind and help every hungry customer to choose food with advice. The cashier is a nice guy and I saw him directing and explaining people about the menu they have.
The place is bit small compared to the crowd that Boon Lay Int expects.
The chilli prata, dosa and samosa tastes good here.
Visit again after relaxation of COVID, the taste maintain as per their standard. Will come again if crazing for prata.

Very good quality zi char food at relatively decent prices. Read the reviews on this place earlier and ordered the pumpkin prawn, salted egg yolk sotong, Marmite pork ribs, smoked duck with jelly fish, and cabbage wrapped chicken in claypot. Really loved the first 4 dishes as they were executed very well! The cabbage chicken was interesting but too soft and drenched in gravy for my liking. Chicken was also a bit dry on the inside. Service was friendly and prompt. Got nice drinks like lemongrass drink and water chestnut which was refreshing. Parking can be a killer here so opt to take public transport or Grab if possible.
Came around 1.30pm not much queue. The spicy ramen is spicy enough but if you are hungry recommend to add extra noodles. Staff very helpful -asked for more spring onions and got them

My wife and I went there for the national day promo. Two mains , half dozen oysters and two durian puffs for 56++.

It was decent. We loved the steaks like usual. The oysters were pleasant. My wife didn't like the sauce on it. But the puffs were warm for some odd reason.
Variety of foods n reasonable pricing
Was in the area and came across this halal stall. Although it's not authentic Japanese, but it's delicious, very homely, portions were good and value for money. It was a satisfying meal.
I order their rice and noodle dishes from here regularly. Food is delicious and portion sizes are generous. Price is very value for money. Highly recommended.
Affordable Japanese stall for students.

Sister restaurant of Kabuke‚Äôs, the concept of this place is somewhat similar. Beef bowls, Uni, Sake. The food here didn‚Äôt blow my mind away, but the service was excellent. We were served by Nareenth and Iris and they were great folks. Their famed Aburi Ootoro hand roll was a massive disappointment, with the seaweed slightly soggy (I ate it almost immediately), Uni obviously not in its best quality and rather tough altogether. Truffle hamachi carpaccio looks nice but I couldn‚Äôt taste any truffle from the pieces itself. Their sliders saved the day for me, along with their service. To be honest, I‚Äôve never liked Kabuke and I dragged my feet to Tanoke. While I‚Äôm glad that I finally checked out Tanoke, I felt the food‚Äôs quality was on the same level as that of Kabuke‚Äôs. For the more discerning customer, you might feel slightly short-changed as everything that‚Äôs supposedly fancy on the menu do not deliver at all in terms of quality and taste. This is the same problem with Kabuke too. I doubt I‚Äôll return again but thanks for the effusive service!
Great food for the price. Hard to find food Mexican fast food in Singapore so this place never fails to satiate that craving
Price is okay. Food taste i find it average overall. It was quite empty inside the restaurant during weekday evening time....
Quite upset as the taste was not as expected ,the soup was salty and the cabbage was not fresh, even rotten.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: ‚ÄúLook for Mee‚Äù good food and friendly service. Authentic home cooked flavours.

One of my go-to places for wanton noodles. Their Pork lard is amazing! Soup is on the peppery side. Char siew is sweet & to my liking.

Price wise, it's $6 for a bowl of noodles with char siew & veg and also comes with a soup containing 3 small wanton.

Good food and reasonable price , big portion .
Value for money. They don‚Äôt charge service charge . Free plain water . Their ice coffee is nice I like it . Will definitely visit again , a lot of parking lot availability as well at HDB carpark , easy to acess location . Seniors citizen have $6.80 meals set , and was told the portion is same as normal price.forgotten to took others food picture , next time update again .
(This was the portion that I had taken up few pcs )üòã
Nice View
Bbq is good. Loved the chicken wings.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: When less crowded you get to enjoy more time. Being chase when there is queue. For a restaurant it is not very customer oriented place
Quite nice, especially when they got promotion

Only problem I have is that number runs out very quickly for the day if you don‚Äôt book early.

They should use the same booking system as sushiro, where you need to go down to the outlet physically to check in again in order to be part of the queue.

Nice food though, been here many times üòÅ

I would have love to have given 2 stars but the beef burger did not fail my taste buds.

Number of onion rings 4!!!!!! Disgusting . Vs amount of fries.

Will I eat another burger here? No.
Friendly staff Nice services.  But product was abit under my expectations. Not going back again.
Food is of worse quality than earlier. Staff was not very helpful. Angus beef was chewy.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Went to eat nearing the closing time. The staff were still rather pleasant and courteous despite that.

The Chargrill and lemon chicken were good. The wedges and onion rings weren't fresh but expected since it was almost closing time.

Overall great experience.

This is a horrible shop. Waited for more than 30 mins still haven‚Äôt got my food‚Ä¶wanted to rate zero star, but there is not such option. :) I asked when the food will be ready, they answered ‚Äúsince you‚Äôve already waited for so long, what‚Äôs the big deal with waiting for additional 5 mins‚Äù, amazing attitude :)
The fish & chips very average

The food, service and menu design feels very authentic and Hokkaido. Portions of food are rich and fulfilling. Customer service was prompt and polite.

A nice halal touch to traditional Japanese food. I will certainly be back again!

Penang Food - tucked in shops opp Toa Payoh HDB hub is a hidden gem. Excellent staffs working hard to serve us fast delicious food too üòÉüôåüèª

Their Assam laksa uses authentic Msia rice noodles. You will never find it anywhere else. Almost like being back in Penang. The gravy is rich and flavourful. Stall is generous with Vege garnish. Very fresh Veges

Thai style fried Sea bass fish is very fresh and appetising too. Crispy on outside, soft tender meat on inside. Highly recommended for sharing üòã

Can try their homemade Ba Long Long juiceüßÉ

For the price, no complains! Best option compared to flying to Penang Msia in this no flying Covid season.

Was there for the 1st time Unorganised and poor customer service.
Food was good!
Not sure if I would visit them again.
Enjoyed a late dinner with Smoked Duck Fried Rice and Gam Hiong Prawn Fried Rice. Generous portion and definitely value for money.

Terrible..
Never seen a restaurant that heats up already made Dosai and heat it up again with more oils and serve it to customer. We are paying high price and we are served like this.
Funny thing is the chef knows that I am seeing and he hiding and do it in a see through kitchen.

Please don't do this in foods and people's please be careful.

I don‚Äôt really anything to complaint about this place. Specialty rolls are super good and I‚Äôm a fan of Ramen üçú and theirs is very good. Prices are a little high but in general acceptable for the location and food quality ‚Ä¶
Ok
Small portions for the price. Porridge was otherwise tasty but lukewarm and had little ingredients.

A Standard Tzechar Restaurant with air condition. As expected the items are more pricey. $18 for cereal prawn, the prawns are not very fresh but still taste good thanks to the cereal. The prawn is big but there is only 5 pieces !

The furong egg taste crispy and flavorful. The prawn paste chicken was crispy and juicy as well. Service was prompt overall the taste is above avg.
Fried rice was oily and awesome. Exactly how a fried rice dish should taste like. The wok hey and the fragrance makes it so delicious!

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Service is great, good ventilation, good food and sauces,  not expensive price. Overall very good experience. üëç Do come and try.

We dine in ichiban for at least once a month and we are always satisfied but this time around, the quality of food degrades. The soup based dish has no taste, the kani roll became small and the ingredients became less, and taste is no longer the same. ‚òπÔ∏è

The tables are stained, not cleaned properly. The glass thingy in the middle in scratched, the room has mould building up around the place. The room inside looks like it hasn't been clean for 5 days or so. The staff is a mess. And the chill we order from the start of the meal didn't even come.

Good and reasonably priced wester food. Portions are also reasonably big. The fish was lightly crumbed and deep fried just nice. Waited more than 10mins, with hardly any customers around‚Ä¶ maybe due to take a ways. Many smokers around though
Truly restaurant standard hawker price. The salmon so big I was surprised it's only $6 per set. And it's delicious too.
Very laid back atmosphere and fantastic food. Prices at the average seafood restaurant level. Chilli crab, prawn vermicelli, peking duck were pretty nice

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Many good food like teo Chew pao, lei char, mee siam, muffins......

Was recommended by a friend and I cannot stop going back.

It‚Äôs definitely a hidden gem and the thai food is bloody legit. The broth for the steamed fish was so refreshing filled with lemongrass, mushrooms and it was invigorating with every sip!

Tom yam soup is definitely one of the better ones here, it‚Äôs thick and not watery just as how it should be.

They‚Äôre generous with the size of the omelette too and to top it off, the owner is such a sweet lady.

The food was average, Orchard central will be a better choice.
The staffs keep wanting to clear our plates when we were still eating‚Ä¶ they will take and throw the cutlery into their trolley. Overall a very bad experience‚Ä¶ I won‚Äôt recommend this outlet.

(Translated by Google) The price is cheap for the Chinese food in the hotel. There is no complaint if it is a beautiful eye and this amount of money. 500 ml of beer comes in properly. Before, the air conditioner worked very well, but here the air conditioner is weak and moderate. As it is a hotel, the toilets are clean and it is a good value, so it is one of the restaurants that I definitely want to visit again.

Variety of options but expensive for sandwich
Food is amazing. Mutton dosai superb and roti paratha good.

Had Penang Prawn noodle - Broth was yummy and stayed warm throughout my meal (of 30mins)
Service was average but seriously it‚Äôs $5 for a very big bowl of delicious food .

it was a very interesting place. I love the chinese pancake with meat in it. their fried rice was really good. you can notice the individual grain of rice. the dumplings were good. but the xiaolongbao was not good. the skin tear up easily and the broth just leaked all out. they should improve from there.

I think I was discriminated against here. I am a regular of Guzman y gomez outlet in Yishun North Point. I always received good service and food from there and expected same from here. I went in at around 11.50, much before lunch rush. There was only one other dine-in customer. Even after 25 mins I didn't receive my order, while customers who came in after me kept getting their orders. When I finally complained, they gave me my order without cutlery or tissue. Will not visit this outlet again.

Fantastic service and authentic Hakka food. We absolutely enjoyed our dinner here. Will definitely return. Our child dropped her fork and the old man (I think must be the owner) came with a new set of cutlery without us asking for it. Very lovely man.

Located in Link@AMK, lies a western stall with a rather extensive menu. Food is self-collected. Tried the Creamy Pasta which was $5.50 but sizeable - pretty affordable.

My only gripe is that the pasta comes with an egg and salad, and when the salad's sauce mixes with the cream in the pasta, it tastes sour and weird. Will prefer if the salad was served separately on the side. Hope to try their meaty stuff one day!

Quite a bad experience over there. Food was so-so nothing too impressive about. We went for the dim sum buffet menu and guess what har gao or shrimp dumpling is not in the dim sum buffet menu and have to ordered separately.

That‚Äôs not the worst, the steam fish come with a strong mud smell but they use large amount of garlic to cover the smell.

The atmosphere is not great even though they are located in a shopping mall the air con in the restaurant is high and there is no cooling feeling.

Lastly, the service. The service is not great at all, no one attended to the table service and our emptied plates are all piling up at the table and no one is here to clear the plates UNTIL when we are about to left the table.

Horrible experience definitely not going back again. There is so many more dim sum place better then them.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Alot of variety and nice food. Staff are very nice too.

One of the best char siews I've had, but the portion of meat is rather small for the price ($4 for char siew rice). Comes with a nice small side of achar though. Beansprouts are delicious, with a generous topping of fried onions and pork lard, but expensive at $4. Dumplings were stuffed incredibly full with a whole prawn and a good amount of meat, but were rather pricey at $4 for 4 as well.
My favourite Indian rojak place.. till now I haven't find anything better than this. Those who visited Northpoint, must give it a try! You will not regret it!

Curry puff is good and has nice spicy kick. Tried both the sardine and potato version. Good for $0.60 and happy to know I‚Äôve got a place nearby!

Bergedil (potato patty) was also yums for $0.50 each! Recommended!

Veggie cucur was also good snack.

Sambal belachan is not as spicy as I‚Äôd expect.

Will definitely consider trying their other dishes as they have quite a queue.

Tried their flat meat soupÊâÅËÇâÊ±§Ôºåkind of expensive for the portion.$13+ they charge 0.5 for container take away. Not authentic at all, the skin is not the kind that real heng hua use. Kind of disappointed!
Food are awesome and delicious at an affordable price

Confirmed and chopped! Authentic push cart dim sum! Besides Red Star, this is the only other place with old style push cart service that I know of. And I have been looking for this on both sides of the border for some time now.

The dim sum still taste good after all these years. Not mind blowingly good but comfortably adhering to the taste you are used to and familiar with. The selection is somewhat limited and this is understandable due to manpower constraints. But they do have all the popular items like Siew Mai, Har Gao, Braised Chicken Feet, Steamed Pork Ribs, Char Siew Buns, Beancurd Skin Wraps, Chee Cheong Fun and Century Egg / Sliced Pork Porridge. Notably missing were Radish Cake and Lotus Leaf Wrapped Glutinous Rice. The one complain I have would be their rule for 90 mins service limit for each table, although I don‚Äôt really see them enforcing it.

Opens from 8am daily so yes, this is the one place in Singapore where you can enjoy a yum cha culture closest to that of Hong Kong. Call it nostalgia but the push cart system is a huge winner for me.
Tastes authentic and good, sells only 2 specific dish but does both so well. Only con was the the lor mee gets watery after eating 30% of it, but flavourwise is great and will definitely come back

Located at the side of the standalone NTUC (not AMK Hub), this quiet cafe secretly sells one of the best nasi padangs. Spice level is just right to tingle the taste buds and the variety of food options is sure to delight.

Dishes go beyond the standard fare, and includes mussels and black squid (usually its chilli squid only).

Situated in a nice quiet location. Shop abit small.

It‚Äôs not very expensive nor very cheap. The fish head soup is abit of bland side though it means no msg too. Fish is quite fresh too.

I don‚Äôt feel very strongly about it‚Ä¶can come can don‚Äôt come.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Really yummy üòã handmade dim sum. Accepts all payment.
Excellent western food. Portion is good and very good customer service.
Cheap and fresh nasi lemak, starting at $1! Great place to hangout on a Saturday morning, soaking in the bustle and liveliness of a heartland üòÅ

Nice setting and Candi took really good care of us. She is attentive to our needs and ensures all our dishes come timely. The popiah and the rest of the dishes we ordered were delicious. Will definitely dine in again!
Very good vegetarian food. Fancy. I loved the tofu and the "cod fish" especially.
Broth is awesome, noodle is very q, and the portion is just nice for a guy. Highly recommended.

Firstly the service there was super attentive. Not forgetting how delicious the food was! This restaurant is great for family gathering.  I enjoyed it so much with my mum and dad. ‚ô° will definitely be back again.
Food is awesome, nice place to hangout for supper too! ‚ò∫Ô∏è

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Bought a seafood mee goreng  charge at 6.50
Gosh the portion was so little I am wondering they think they are serving a 2 years old child food portion?

There are some dishes taste ok but in general very salty. The most disappointing part is the service. The waitress ladies look extremely confused, multiple different staff randomly dropped by asking random questions such as ‚Äúany of you ordered beer?‚Äù seriously... The tea tasted really bad. Really a horrible pot of tea honestly.

Pretty good food and service at reasonable prices. The rosti waffles were very delicious, although we wish they could be even crispier. Pancakes are fluffy, scrambled egg is creamy, bacon is not too greasy. The melon tea smells very calming although the melon taste itself wasn't very strong. The online ordering platform was missing photos for several items, which made it hard to visualize what the dish would look like or the portion size.

Relaxing simple decor. The outdoor area is pet-friendly, lotsa cute dogs there! Indoors has plenty of seating. There is also a small garden area on the other end, with goldfishes swimming around in a little rock fountain.
Lovely place to dine in. Great selection of Asian cuisines at affordable prices. Cooling place but gets a little stuff though bearable.

Decided to walk in on a Sunday lunch. We were lucky to get a table but do expect to queue. Service was good, non pushy. Food in general was very tasty, though you may feel thirsty later in the day. Portioning is adequate. Pricing was fair. Decor is a little on the old side. Parking can be a slight challenge but manageable.

Omg I'm so shocked that all the food is so tasteless and super bad. Not expecting it until we ate it and I saw the review/rating and we waited for 1hr for it . Tako is rock hard and same for the fries. All the rice is so bland plus it keeps falling apart, the sashimi also gone case cause it's room temp and not fresh. By far the worst Japan restaurant ever. What ultimate sushi satisfaction? Yucks!!!

(Translated by Google) The store is easy to enter even by one person with just the right distance to the store and the customer service of the store owner.

Chicken Chop with Fries and Coslaw with brown sauce. The chicken is well done and juicy inside.
Really love Genki sushi. Finally‚Ä¶ an outlet in Jurong point! If only the outlet is bigger.. the waiting time can be shorten üòÄ
Great samsui chicken and hearty Chinese herbal soups. Perfect for family dinners and a cosy get together. Food often consistent. Queues expected on weekends.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Asked for more mayo on my youtiao and he squeezed the whole mayo OVER my whole plate with my spring rolls. Eh trying to be funny???? Who eats spring roll with mayo?? Problematic!!
Comfortable seating, nice food at reasonable price

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
The place was packed.

Wedges tasted fresh, the steak and incrediburger were good.

The mac and cheese was so-so.

1 nonya fish head
1 assam fish
1 vege
1 salted egg sotong
1 roasted chicken
1 pork knuckle
1 har cheong gai

All these for only around $100. Amazing! And the food was rather tasty too. I liked the salted egg sotong!

Consistently yummy & fresh sushi and sashimi; even their edamame is served warm and slightly salted. Prices are just a tad high compared to other mainstream Japanese restaurant chains, but it's worth the food quality and pleasant service. ‚Ä¶
It is so frustrating that i order pratawala through grab and came with a missing fried chicken. How am i supposed to eat?? Called the store to no avail. This will be the last

We had dinner there and the food was excellent. The service was quick. I have yet to go to a restaurant where all the food is served within 15mins. Only spoiler was it was a family night and a few screaming kids spoil it a bit for us.
Food was average. Service is slow, but servers were friendly and helpful. Managed to change the potato to more salad.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Very good service with amazing food. The bendi masala is a must!

This is really the best mookata I have ever had!
Great food great service!
Marination is awesome!!!

content:
Been here 3 times in the last 5 days.

Recommended is the pork fry with green chili another cauliflower dish which I didn‚Äôt take a photo of and the popcorn chicken.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: This Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang is delicious with it spicy gravy and they have a lots of variety to choose.
Very good place in side the NTU, the packed pasta was different from others and very nice. Best value for students and service also good and quick, must visit place
Super chewy prata and high quality curry for a good value. Definitely a hit for a Sunday brekkie.
This is my sec time here, I enjoyed the food very much, service is very good, I would like to come back here again.
