restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Food is decent but on the pricey side. Paid $200+ for 4 pax. Ordered 3 main dishes, 1 noodle dish and 1 dimsum appetizer.

Service is average. Asked for a nicer table during reservation as it was a special occasion, but the restaurant didn‚Äôt make any effort here. They even sat us super near the kitchen.

Paid $3.50 for single entry parking.

Mmmmmmmmmh. This was my first time here and thumbs up for one of the better steaks that I've tasted in awhile. Tender juicy medium rare ribeye steak that is made to perfection.

I must say the black pepper sauce is indeed unique, not too peppery and just generally great to enjoy it with the steak.

The complement fried potato side dish is very unique and tasty as well. Will come back and try the other menu items next!

The best compliment I can give this chain is that it's the Jamie Oliver of Mexican food. Proudly underwhelming, uninspired, overpriced yet somehow, you'll find one everywhere. While i can see how they might appeal to the undemanding and uninitiated, there is definitely much, much better Mexican food out there (and yes even in SG).
Oiishi bread very expensive as compared to Cedele & Baker & Cook..their sourdough bread too holey

Meticulous service with tasty heng hwa food! Mum and I enjoyed our lunch tremendously. Heng Hua lor mee was cooked well and tasty. The peranakan stir-fry veg was cooked well with wok hei and had yam bits! Fried fish is crispy and nice. Thank you.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: The star dish, Ayam Taliwang is blessed with a chili that is a veritable storm of spiciness stir fried in with the fragrant dried shrimp. More power than Boon Lay's nasi lemak if you're looking for a kick!

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Great taste of the food, the view was good as well.
The weather was hot but peggy was so friendly. She catered to the queue outside while even helping to take drinks for the people sitting. Wonderful service!

Good and tasty food served.
Value for money and lots of freshly fried vegetables in different style.
Only one point that to higjlight.....its always long queue especially lunch tim

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Love it!
I just got back from Jeju and was missing Tangsuyuk so much. Not black pork but I enjoyed the dish so much. $53 for Tangsuyuk, Mandu, Jjamppong & Jjajiangmyeon (SET A)
Bonus is that they have baijiu and also Korean alcohol available.
Wonderful Chinese food here. Love the beef! Very specific menu, and they do every dish to perfection

Sets in a nice corner of the coffee shop and charges a reasonable price for the authentic taste of good Tonkotsu broth. The young man is friendly and entertained last minute change of broth. We will definitely support again.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: One of the better roasted meat/chicken rice stalls in the North Eastern part of SG. Their char siew is very good.
Milo taste watery , got a hair on prata

The first I came here, I could not get in as it was full and waiting time was waay too long for my hangry self. This time, I came on a weekday evening. At 8pm the place was half full giving me ample space choices. I chose to sit out. The food was good, not great but the prata was the star of the show. I had ordered chicken masala, which is a chefs recommendation but I did not like it that much. The mutton dishes and the plain gravy that came with the prata was nice!

Ate here on Hari Raya Puasa 2pm, did not realize their last order was 230pm! Enjoyed the pork collar (not shown), very yummy not spicy and not too greasy. Tom yum was too salty and spicy for our liking. But the main dishes were great. Ambience was similar to that of Bangkok outdoors, but cleaner (of course in sg).

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
First and the last time dining here, service is awfully bad, staffs are not attentive although not much diners at that point of time.

Staffs are having lunch together and talking happily disregarding the customers in the vicinity. Nothing wrong to have lunch but I suggest having lunch at different timing rather than having lunch altogether.

Rice also tasted sour, almost feels like mayonnaise with rice.
Ok - nice lunch there.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Happened by chance, but found the best Bee Hoon Goreng Puteh in J9. Finally! Ikan bilis was crispy and flavorful. Enough veggies and red chillies. Ummmmph. Egg fluffy with yolk runny. Service was quick. Will be back

Six months later. Still my favourite.  But think they raised prices a little. $5 for my bee hoon puteh.

Update 6 Nov 2019:  They have changed to the usual Islamic restaurant mode of cash collection: pay at a dedicated cashier counter. A bit chaotic, tried to charge me for things someone else ordered. And my bee hoon goreng puteh's standard dropped.

Update 9 December 2019: the nasi biryani is good. Mutton soft, well marinated, basmati rice fresh, egg ok. Papadum not crispy anymore and acha so so. Overall good meal at $6.50

I had the Italian herb chicken fried rice and it was very tasty! Rice was very flavourful on its own and luckily the cashier lady told me to have less chili for this. Totally agreed with her after tasting the rice. Chicken was tender and not dry. Other half had the smoked duck fried rice which tasted better with the chili but still good. Definitely would return again to try other dishes.
Pork chops was easily one of the best i have ever had in a food court.

Tom yam soup was horribly salty.  Totally Inedible. Chicken in green curry not fresh too. We have to drive all the way back to the toa payoh outlet with the food n ask for a refund. Disappointed. Not recommended

Shocking customer experience and mediocre food.
Should have check out the reviews first instead of just walking in. Will give 0 star if I could.
Went there with my son because he thought the prata looks good but boy, were we in for a nasty surprise!
Staff came over and shouted at him saying he was eating too slow and other people are waiting for the table.
There was only two people queuing, that might be eating in or taking away. But there was a few other tables that are empty.
Regardless, we did not just order one drink and sit there chatting. He just a young child and to be shouted at with these remarks is really appalling.
The reviews on customer service and quality shows a very clear indication that something needs to be done with training and managing of the quality otherwise prata wala will soon be PRATA WAN DAN soon!
Cod fish not cooked, chili mud crab very small. Not much variety of food to choose

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: I found this place by chance.  But I m very impressed with the tempeh.   It is fried, crunchy and give your taste bud a "yummy,  that's is good".  Tempeh got a caramel taste, just right for the sweetness.  I ate a vegetarian dish that day.  But my 3 other friends took a portion of their mutton dish and said its good too.  Pricing is fair and portion are large.  Sorry I didn't get a photo of our food.  But believe me, if u are in that area, it's worth a try.  Their service is fast and the staff are friendly.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Its a pretty good Dim Sum place that isnt Swee Choon! Their baked goods are the best the bbq pork puff if I remember the name right. Only thing is queues are long, and there isnt much seats, and today was fine. But before Covid, the queues to get food and finding a seat is long! Be prepared!  But worth it~

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Reasonable price but dim sum is average, except for bbq pork pau which is quite tasty. Lotus leaf glutinous rice tastes bland and hard, probably need longer steaming time.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: One of my favorite Chinese restaurant in the town. Cheap and delicious
Spacious, comfortable and good ambience restaurant located in the ITE! Good customer service and friendly staff, recommend us a lot of signature dishes! Highly recommended!!
Restaurant tucked away in Sembawang, small outlet, but the owner really friendly. The Indian Clay pot was spot on, mutton Clay pot I had was spicy, but damnnnn good and the chai was amazing as well.

(Translated by Google) Mother's Aroi

(Original)
Aroi mak mak

Loved the meal here. The store is dated, but the food is excellent. You get a fantastic Indian restaurant meal at such affordable price. The fried mushroom is a must try. Prawn Satti Soru is sufficient for 2-3 persons, and it's the brilliant and extensive count of prawns. The curry fish is fury but great for people like me who are into spicy food.

First time trying their food. Ordered a pork chop fried rice, both the fried rice and pork chop is tasteless. Wok hey easily taste so much better. And they charge 50 cents for a regular take away box. Take your money somewhere else.
We tried a number of Thai restaurant, the food here are pretty ok..the omelette is good but 5pcs of Thai fishcake for $18.90 is expensive...
Had the beef rendang and enjoyed it. It's a smallish place and it's always crowded, so you have to queue up. But the food is worth it and affordable.
mala taste ok, waited one full hour for our food, and we realized that most of our ingredients amount got cut! and some ingredients we took were missing! we paid $30 for one small bowl! unacceptable!
My all time favourite Chinese diner! Tried almost the menu and all taste surprisingly good! Highly recommended!

Great place for a quiet lunch during peak hour in the CBD area.

Tried their peking duck, it was slightly different from the usual dish, duck meat is sliced and wrapped together. Not as crispy but still good. Love their salted vegetable fish soup, thou it is slightly oily.
Amazing nasi lemak and loved the a la carte options. And the fried chicken ‚Äî crunchy and fresh! Super sweet service from the women working there too. Thank you! Will definitely be back.
Good value for a pint of beer and good outdoor seating area. However service was slow and seemed like an inconvenience to staff. Could do better.
Something more than I expected and the food delicious. Especially their signature ribeye steak with merlot butter. I will come back with friends and recommend it to others.
The fish porridge is superb! Very flavorful! Gonna try for new goers! Their seafood porridge too! Ordered 2 porridge and good for 3 pax sharing! Will go back again!
Superb! Love the butter masala prawns, fish head curry, mutton, vegs... basically everything! Food is also reasonably priced. Must visit!

We came near closing and were welcome in.

Tonight dinning is fantastic, great service and delicious food but wondering if msg was a little over as We felt really thirsty after the meal

Parking
You can park inside Macpherson mall n walk over.

Will we be back?
Yes!  Food is nicer,  we just have to drink more water!
Wide variety of sticks to choose from, at affordable prices and four types of sauces to dip into. Happiness!
Good food and friendly service. The peking duck was excellent and delicious.

After 10 years of being his customer, food is still good and delicious. Never fail to impress me. For a successful place he has, the boss Tom is still a very humble man, still hands-on at his own place and provides great service. Not overly priced western and Nepalese food. Definitely a good place for a good cravings fix.
Great food and good services ~~

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Mediocre meats but the sauces are not too bad

suka2 don't want to open. came on tuesday, 02 nov, and not open even tho stated on google maps that it is.

NOT the first time either, even when the stated day of rest is every friday.
Good

Enjoyed the food and service. They introduced 30-50% on signature dishes during the stabilisation phase so quite worth it. Had the curry fish head - half at $18++ portion was big. Garlic pork, squid with ladies finger also tasty.
Reasonable food and pricing.

A long time player in the western food circle, that I finally chanced upon. My hotplate steak was rather forgettable in my opinion, just ordinary. I was completely underwhelmed. It wasn't a good value to boot.
A small but nice Indian Muslim restaurant. the Roti Prata one of the best around the area. the mutton soup is normal...not salty enough for me.
A very fun and interactive team bonding place. A must try social and corporate event...
Big pau skin like char siew pau, too low gluten. Very little content inside. Cannot compare with kopitiam or nam kee
Nice foods recomended.should try the satti surru
Nice north Indian food especially the garlic naan and butter panner masala.... Cosy place to dine in...

Since we can't go Malaysia, chance upon this lok lok place. They open late! So for all the supper eaters like us!! Do order the satay sauce when you are there! Friendly lady boss. We choose ala cart as we didn't felt we could eat alot.

Do go for the buffet if you're a big eater, much more worth it !:)

We had the chicken soup and peanut sauce. We also love the bbq option. Must better than the other coffee shops fried greasy options (ps they do have option of fried as well).

Will definitely return back with friends once dining restriction ease!!:)
The food is fresh, environment and service are great... Especially the taste of the soup üëç
Overall it's nice and yummy Nasi Lemak! Shiok Chili and delicious bergedil! But sometimes the rice still little bit, tiny winny hard..

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: One of the better "Hong Kong Street" food in Singapore. Most of the dishes are pretty good, except the Assam Fish head. It is really bad.
Booked 6 table on Saturday, the service was good and fast. Food was also very nice and tasty with reasonable price.

1. Very slow service
2. Sometimes closes before the stated time
3. If ordering during non-peak hours, the food can be soggy and not fresh

Highly recommend to wait if you see not more than one person in the queue.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Nice place for a very early hearty breakfast. Surprised to see they open really early and almost all  dishes are ready. Got there at around 640am and its already abuzz, satisfied with the food quality.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: The food was really good I ordered Tandoori chicken Naan set, It was very descent  It came witha delious gravy

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: A couple that certainly takes pride in what they serve. Not just the food but respect for the customers. Greeting seniors respectfully ... keep it up.

Very good briyani if you are there during lunchtime.  Freshly made soft, moist basmati rice, chkn/mutton coated w thick tasty masala dry curry.  Served w pappadum  cucumber salad n dalcha curry.üëç.  Must share w another if not ask for less rice.  Dun like carbo coma.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Today I was at this place Q 1 hour just for this yummy UGGLI muffins. I started to Q @ 11.50am and finally my turn ut was 12.52pm. Now 1 person is allowed to buy 1 box of 12 muffinsüëçüëç. Do drop by to buy these tummy muffins but do remember u must have the patient to wait. Yummy üòãüòãüßÅ
Not So good food .. chicken and curry was  smelly.

first time visit. ordered crabs, pork ribs, hotplate tofu and sweet potato veg. overall food is very good. will come again to try their signature assam fish head. Gu Ma is very friendly and recommended other dishes for us to order in the next visit

Despite the 10 min wait to eat during lunch hour, we were well attended to by Peggy. She offered to have my son stand in the restaurant area as it was really hot outside and gave him tissue to wipe his sweat. It might look like a 2 star eatery with 5 star level of warmth and hospitality.
The duck is not bad... The pork chops here with the green chilli sauce are really delicious! üëç

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Ordered first time to try this new restaurant suggested by my friend. Good and tasty food at affordable price. Highly recommend üëç

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Were here for reunion dinner. Environment is good. Pricy, but the food taste is averageÔºå Sea cucumber is very hard‚Ä¶  yee mian is salty‚Ä¶
Yummy Thai food. Added extra dishes on top of the premium value set. Total bill about 130 for 5 pax.
Authentic food at economical price. Quite crowded at meals time.. better call to reserve in advance.
San lou hor fun was really good, but the slice fish bee hoon only had a lot of fish slices going for it.

Worst food ,I order nasi goreng  it's taste like spice rice no even necessary Vegas in the rice,  only  got lot of spices ,no tasty, cold food they charge 5.90$ never give cucumber also.Normal kopitiam  is more  better to eat nasi goreng  instead of this Prata Wala shop.
Ordered murtaburger via grabfood. What i receieve was what i assume is nasi brani, come on how do you screw up something like this.
Yummy and cheap china food. Highly recommended

This outlet has the best service so far. Putien‚Äôs staffs are generally very service oriented, you get good service at any outlet you visit. Am here for my favourite white cabbage soup tonight besides the usual good stuffs.
Good services and good food. Really friendly staffs
Taste and prices are good. Promo crab and sea bass are really good value.
We celebrated Mother's Day at Gim Tim and my parents enjoyed the meal! Food is good and the charges are reasonable.
Dim sum is ok. Only can takeaway. Ordering and pickup system is similar to fast food outlets.
Food is served hot and fast! Excellent service! Great place to celebrate occasions. Friendly staff and bosses

Another ordinary Chinese restaurant but with commendable customer service. Perfect Peking duck should be sliced thinly with nearly no meat sticking on the skin. Whereas, what they serve is just the opposite‚òπÔ∏è. The rest of the food is just fine.. üôÇ #msgreedysis #greedybuddiez

(15th June '22, ~5.45pm)
It's the best dried mala hotpot I've ever tasted in SG!! The spice is out of this world I'd say! For this 2nd visit, we increased our portion up to Abt $65 for the 2 of us, with the usual stuff we love. Spiciness still remain at small which is just the right amount for us to enjoy.

They offer to separate the fried stuff such as luncheon meat, fish and potato (sliced and fried into chips). You won't regret just DO IT. Add a buncha eggs to get them scrambled and watery down onto your bowl. Also preferred the smaller noodles while the sauce dances intensely ard them. Slurp carefully! The Thai milk tea is a must-have. THICK is the word. Add a little bit of water as it's Abit too sweet for me.

Pretty nice of u guys to include extra ingredients such as fried fish in our pot during our 1st visit. Will be back for more cravings!

Worst service ever experienced. Waiter served dessert right after our starter. We declined having it and he rolled his eyes. It wasn‚Äôt a busy night but didn‚Äôt refill our cup of water. Requested to make order for takeaway but didn‚Äôt come back. Returned the same plate of dessert with melted ice cream at the end of our meal. Requested to change the ice cream. Came back with messy plates smeared with the melted ice cream around the plate, and added new ice cream on top of it. Served without spoons. Had to wait for spoons. Embarrassing cause I brought my bosses to this restaurant. Never coming back.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
We found this place was fairly well rated and their pics looked pretty good too, soo we ventured out to give it a go - boy, we were so happy we did!!
.
The decor isn‚Äôt like super insta-flashy or anything but that made it appeal even more to us as a place that just did good food well üëçüèª
.
We were surprised they did crabs ü¶Ä as well so definitely had to give them a go too. We ordered:
~ 2x Singapore Chilli Crabs
~ Whole Hainan Chicken
~ BBQ pork
~ Belachan Kang Kong
.
Let‚Äôs start with the crab. It was amazing! Loads of roe, meaty and the sauce was epic. It was perfect to soak up with the fried mantou (buns). Luckily we got 2 cos we completely demolished them (probably could have done another 2 lolol üòèü§≠)
.
The chicken was good too, most of it was super tender, just a few breast pieces that were a touch on the ‚Äúwell cooked‚Äù side but overall tasted great üëçüèª
.
The kang kong veggies were super yummy too. Love eating these kinds of veggie dishes in Asian countries cos it‚Äôs super inexpensive but very very yummy and full of wokchi üî•üî•
.
A lovely place that we‚Äôre glad we tried out and to our surprise had amazing crabs ü¶Ä as well as the chicken üêì

NOT YOUR USUAL WESTERN HAWKER FOOD.
Their medium rare steak is perfect!
so tender and delicious.
Sauces are very generous and goes well with the meat.
Curly fries are golden crispy perfection.
You can really tell that the food is prepared like restaurant-level style.
And the best of all, price is very reasonable! üëåüèªüëçüèªüëèüèª

Nothing to shout about. Was a little overwhelming after a few bites. We also requested for the crispy red bean pan cake to be serve after our other food, but everything came one shot. The crispy red bean pan cake isn't crispy and it tasted ‚Ä¶
Awesome services with very delicious food ! Recommend to bring your family to have your meals here !! Will definitely come back again üëçüèª

Food is expensive and tables are super dirty - they are so sticky that the paper napkins are ripped apart when u try to use them after dinning. Also, plse note you cannot use both SAFRA card and SAFRA vouchers together - which the other F&B outlets in SAFRA allow.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
Horrible service! The rude waitress made us wait on a dirty table for 15 mins. When we walked to the counter to ask politely if we could order, they told us to go back to our seats and wait. Very poor service! This is despite the fact that there were not many diners.
Will never return again

Had the worst experience here. The Milo tasted so watery.. overcharged me with a fish and chicken for $8 when we asked why she reduce the price to $7.80. the tehc was watery too.. won't come back again
Tried unagi and pork jowl combo don, unagi was a tad fishy, while pork jowl was great with good combination of fats n meat. Overall pretty tasty but the sauce can be overpowering towards the end.

Reman located in the hawker.
Their Chashu very nice! Big portion.
Also highly recommend for their Gyoza!

We were invited by a friend to have dinner at her neighborhood's Indian restaurant, Tasha's. The restaurant itself is bright and clean, simple layout. Ordered to share. Their claypot fish head curry was fresh, though we wished the gravy was less diluted. Masala squid was a yummy rice-topper. Prices are easy-on-the-wallet too.
Elaborate Menu , good service. Food tastes good. Pocket friendly restaurant, No GST, No Service Tax. For sure, will go again. Will recommend everyone to try at least once üôÇüôÇüôÇ

This is my first time commenting. Please don't visit this restaurant.

They don't serve rice, no ginger for Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖ, vinegar is diluted. The ÁΩóÊ±âÂØ® which costs $10 is canned button mushrooms in a watery gravy. Ëå≠ÁôΩÁÇíËÇâ‰∏ù has no ËÇâ‰∏ù. 1 dish didn't arrive. All the meat is canned. Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖ and ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖ tasted frozen. And I haven't even mentioned the lacking service.

I just try the Penang lor mee (Malaysia) , the taste and quality I can give 70% like Penang .....

content: Lovely experience here! Food is good and not too oily
Food are way to ex. It's normal as zi cha
Gotta try their dimsum!!
Superb

Interesting place for plant based and vegetarian dishes. Very good range of rice, noodles, dishes and dim sum. Food is pretty decent - like the Hong Kong Ee Fu noodles and the rojak. Good range of soups as well. The set meal for 2 pax is also a good option that includes dim sum and a combination of other dishes and soup.
Never seen a udon like this. Very different from the menu. The soup was cloudy because of the beef. Beef was not fresh at all.
Old.school western food. Love the pork chop especially

You can‚Äôt really complain for the price and quality you get. Tenderloin on a hot plate for $18 is a steal. Meat was tender and substantial. Not like those thin slices you often get from hawker centres they charge you $10 for. Probably one of the best old school steak places you can find anywhere.
Slow service

Came here as a family group for birthday celebration. Food quality is expected given the price. Place is not crowded even though it is Sunday weekend lunch time. The server will share his opinions and to me may seem a bit too talkative. Otherwise I'll score it a bit more for service. There is no option for air conditioned seats so come prepared. BTW, it's now named tasty loong. Had problem finding the place until we noticed the new name plastered over the poster. It may be under new management.

There are other options available around the vicinity if you are looking for family friendly seafood restaurants so it's going to be tough for the rebranded restaurant.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
I went on a Sat and got seated at 1730hrs as it was fully book for the later seating. As we ordered quite a lot for 4 pax, we left at around 2045hrs. In between we still add dishes and that's why it took longer for us to finish it. There were very professional and only tell us that they needed the table back during dessert time.

Their food still taste the same as olden times so there is nothing to rave about. It's still as good as ever. If you have foreign guests can bring them there as it's quite traditional but yet classy due to the decorations. Its one of the more expensive place in town.

Ordered: ($370)
- mixed platter
- pomfret (700g)
- drunken chicken
- pork ribs (4 pieces, must order individually)
- fried kway teow
- french bean
- 4 individual desserts
- pot of tea

Found this on google map and decided to give it a go! We ordered Thai Basil Rice, Olive Fried Rice, Kailan with Mushroom, Tomyam Seafood Soup (Creamy) & Red Ruby as dessert. Everything was good especially the Tomyam! Total damage - $26.80, very affordable! We will be back to try the Steam Seabass with Thai Lime Sauce ü§§

Chinese fusion food. Servings are good for 4 pax. Enjoyed prawn bonito aioli, wuxi pork ribs, lamb tenderloin and roast duck. Quiet ambience and private seating. Highly recommended and wiuld definitely return

I have been to this place since as long as I can remember. A native to Toa Payoh, this stall was formerly at the corner of  Block 125 coffeeshop, back in the 80s. Yes I do agree sometime the price can be slightly pricey as to compare to some other stalls calling themselves Nasi Padang when it just a mixed rice stall. Well if you want to eat something good, authentic it's a good price to pay as Che Rose Nasi Padang serves authentic Nasi Padang that is on the same par as those you can find in Padang, Sumatra. Don't just take my words, you have to try it yourself. My personal favorite would be the Squid, Rendang (beef & chicken) also their Gulai Ayam.

Small place within Tunglok Seafood restaurant. Best to do booking.
Yummy food.

Douraku Kaiseidon Set($38++)
Uni, Hokkaido Scallop, Botan Ebi, Maguro, Salmon and Ikura over a bed of sushi rice on that day. Sashimi were fresh and thick cut.
Served with chawanmushi, miso soup, refreshing salad of the day & dessert of the day.

Legendary Wagyu Don Set($36++)
Not legendary at all. The aburi wagyu tataki beef taste was great with chef's special teriyaki sauce but texture was well-done. What an instant disappointment. Foie Gras was sinful and fatty. Served with koshihikari rice, deep-fried garlic chips, sous vide egg, nori, pickles and radish.
Set comes with salmon sashimi, miso soup, salad of the day & dessert of the day.

Eihire($15)
Dried stingray. Texture was chewy with a taste of savoury and oceanic sweet note.
Cheap and good halal Japanese food

Exceptional customer service from the elderly uncle here. However everyone else when he is not around is absolutely horrible. Manager walks passes avoiding eye contact so she doesn‚Äôt have to attend to customers wanting to make orders. Other staff looks like they are overworked or just woken up, it‚Äôs a pain to get any of their attention, even when the store is less than 20 percent filled. Hit or miss experience here
The basil chicken with egg rice is nice and generous in portion. My friends love the crab omelette very much. I personally feel that it‚Äôs tasted better hot. So do eat it hot if you order it.
The staff at the counter is very rude and poor service.

I am from Shanghai family and I feel I'm qualified to comment.
First, I was attracted by the menu as I can tell immediately many are Shanghai home kitchen type dishes that only serve in Shanghai street style small restaurants, like curry beef, sticky rice stick.
Here are the comments:
Service - robotic but no real customer attention.
Xiao long bao and Sheng jian bao - not good the meat is too hard, like a meat ball, and not juicy enough.  I don't agree with one review that it is too oily.  First the "juice" is not oil, it is pig skin boil long enough to become collagen so if anyone has tiny little common sense will know these bao is good for skin and beauty.  If you think it is oily then you better go eat burger.  Here the XLB skin is so thick and dry.  The SJB is not hot and bottom not crispy, just like toast.  The pork not only hard but with no pork taste.  Very disappointed, and if a restaurant will have signature dish disappointed, I can write off this restaurant.
Curry beef rice vermicelli - surprisingly good and authentic and it gives one star in my overall three stars ranking.
Last, as from photo, I am also very disappointed they put the vinegar on the Xiao long bao, do they respect the food or have any sense of hygiene?
Definitely no need to come again.

OK. So the redeux is nice.  It looks nice and the menu is better.
Margarita tasted like pure juice and sour which was a bummer.

As for the food, I think they are missing the best point of having a SW US or Mexican menu:  You only have to stock 10-15 ingredients to make DOZENS of
different southern dishes!!!

My suggestion, and I mean this with best intentions.
Offer plain everything in the menu, then make proteins add-ons.  You are punishing vegetarians by charging full price to remove the meat.  Or even punishing anyone that isn't in the mood for a particular protein.
Adding a surcharge to change proteins is not cool.  2 bucks extra to sub prawn for chicken is kinda crazy.
Go basic + add-ons is my best suggestion.

Best of luck to you!
Friendly and excellent Food w√†s delicious and reasonably priced Second visit was better with more dishes all of which tasted good especially bitter gourd 65 and reasonably priced
Nice foods and the laopan niang very friendly.

Love the duck here. Food is good. The service is very good!! The staff is attentive and polite. They checked to see if we have food allergies & explained some of the dishes to us. I dropped a pair of chopsticks and they replaced it before I could even call for help.
Ordered the roast pork, char siew and roast duck. The roasted meats were very good.
Excellent restaurant situated in ITE Ang Mo Kio. Dishes are exquisitely prepared. Must go and try. Their pu er tea is super special mixed with glutinous rice. Lobsters are really something!

(Translated by Google) Hidden gem for malaysian food. Delicious dough!

(Original)
Hidden gem for malaysian food. Sedap doh!

A underrated place located on Level 2. We went to this place purely from word of mouth. It‚Äôs a Japanese place operated by Thais and they also serve Pok√® bowls which are affordable and delicious. Definitely recommend heading to this shop for lunch!

Came at 8.30pm with seats available. Good ambience, great staff and super good food. Sushi was one of the best I've had in Singapore, expensive but very worth it. Black pork is super flavourful as well. Will definitely come again, highly recommended! Opens till late (around midnight) so great for drinks and hanging out with friends.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
Though a little out of the way, am so glad we gave this place a try! For the very reasonable price, the mookata was great (particularly enjoyed the garlic chicken n beef)! The place was bright n airy, with more than adequate safe distancing between tables. The extremely high level of hygiene was also a huge plus for me - hot plate looked pristine, table was wrapped with a sheet before food was served, kitchen looked spick n span. Service was warm n friendly too. 10/10 would visit again!

Understand that patronage has dipped recently due to the surge in omicron in the community. Do support them! :)

Went to this restaurant on Monday with my family for lunch.

We ordered 2 Smoked Duck Lemak Cili Padi Linguine, 1 Laksa Goreng Barramundi, Cereal Fish and Chips and Malayan Satay Supreme Pizza for mains.

We got complimentary Malayan Wings for starters and Ondeh-ondeh cake for dessert.

All the food was very good and tasty. Portions are big and filling.

We were served by Firdaus, the Manager and Alexa, who rendered us with good service and suggestions.

Will definitely come back again in future, God willing.
The food is uniquely done! Items to take note are the steaks, mashpotato that are fried into ball shape but soft on the inside and the fried chicken wing that is a must eat!

Both of us have been loving their food since we first patroned tiong bahru mall outlet. My second time trying out at Novena Velocity outlet and they have even more varieties! Yummy food and drinks at affo|Singapore prices! Recommended their fried rice, xinghua beehoon, garlic cucumber, teh c and kopi cüòç

Pratas were served crispy but for some pratas there was something off about the texture - like it had been reheated / refried. Curry was nice but abit diluted compared to another branch that I visit, so it isn‚Äôt as shiok.
Teh tarik is really nice here.
Service is slow during weekends, waiting + queuing time >25mins as they have to cater for delivery orders and walk in orders.
Prices also recently increased for some items on the menu by 50cents to a dollar based on a flyer I saw.
Service is extremely bad especially the ladyboss. Totally different with Melaka structure. Menu is very confusing, the segregation of buffet and ala Carte not writing clearly. No next visit anymore!

High cost for a small portion. The dish on left is $15 butter chicken and on right is $7 Samosa Chat. Taken for a ride. Since not many options for Indian food at NTU this restaurant is extorting people.
The restaurant used to be good few years ago even though it was charging above average charge then the quality was good.
Now just pure extortion.

If I could I would give 2.5 stars.
Rounding up because this place is new and I understand they are finding their footing.

Visited on 8 June
Ordered Pan Fried Bun (4pc $5.80) and Xiao Long Bao (5pc $5.80)
It's nice that the listed price was the price I paid, no GST, no service charge. Not sure if this would change.

Pic: Unfortunately found a hair in the meat filling of the pan fried bun.
Pic: panfried buns as served + vinegar colour
Pic: discolouration on the white base piece of xiao long Bao tray

Vinegar provided was very diluted and ginger strips very very mild. I love my vinegar so if you don't you would not mind.

Pan Fried Bun - bottom is definitely nice-crispy, dough to meat ratio is not that bad. My issue was more how to consume it because I wanted to drip vinegar inside + eat as a whole to enjoy the different textures.
Butbthe filling was quite hot (mine were served fresh&hot, some reviews mentioned lukewarm food) and I didn't want the soup inside to spill out so it was a bit awkward trying to bite the bread part open and cool the inside down. After which it was still slightly too big to stuff the whole thing in my mouth.

I cannot speak for authenticity as I have not been to Shanghai to eat the panfried bun (nor to any part of China unfortunately).

Next, I will compare the xiao long Bao to the OTHER brand I visit (Din..).

BY COMPARISON, this one is cheaper, slightly bigger (I say so because I usually put the whole XLB in my mouth) but like a rougher made cousin, skin is not as thin and tender which speaks of lesser skill from the maker, meat is also less "exquisite". For instance, when I bite open Din's XLB, I never see the cooked blood on the filling (that jellyfish, smooth, patchy thing?).

ON ITS OWN, I'm happy to eat it. Would I go back? Not on my own, very unlikely. If my friends wanted to try it, I would go along and be happy/have no complaints, I would take the chance to try another dish probably. Perhaps it's time to research good pan fried bun in SG haha.

This food stall serves the most authentic Thai cuisine by far.
The food is always fresh and tasty, whether it is takeaway set meal or dine-in ala carte dishes.
Was pleasantly surprised that the Thai lady boss cling wrapped the plastic container of green curry that I takeaway and eliminated the common problem of spillage. Strange that other hawkers don't do the same.

Standard of the place has dropped overall.
1. First they did not serve (or even ask, for that matter) water. It was only after about 20 mins after we asked for water that it was served.
2. Then they forgot to serve us the soup that came with the set meal. After we asked they took awhile to verify with each other whether anyone did serve the soup. Eventually arrived after the main course did.
3. One of us ordered the steak well done, and it was so tough that he had difficulties cutting it with the steak knife.
4. For some reason they were reluctant to clear the table. Many service staff walked past and looked to see if we were done eating, but despite the obvious empty dishes, no one bothered to clear. When they served the coffee and ice cream there was not enough space on the table but yet the staff still tried to put the cups and bowls down without clearing, until we had to ask them to do so. Seriously?
5. The steak was supposed to come with slices of King mushroom. The plural only meant there were two pieces instead of one. And superbly thinly sliced too, at that. Have to admire the skill of the chef.

Will seriously reconsider whether to come back here ever again.

(Translated by Google) The food is very delicious. It's like eating in Thailand.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Good food, great Staffs...
We have this "table captain" Hock something...  Who is attentive...  My friend drop a chopsticks and bowl loudly one the floor and voila!!! He rush to us and hand up another one set and rush off to another task..

$1 per stick only. Price is good.

Enoki roll after fried seem to overcooked until the enoki mushroom become very small but taste good üëç just too small.

They also provide many different dips to eat with the skews.
Extremely long waiting time (45mins) for ONE nasi goreng. All others ordering rojak got served 1st. Not recommended if you are in a rush.

Yes. prata was soft like flower and the fish curry is the icing. no other curries allowed!!! or not worth it.  parking was available at 11.20am with normal car park charges.

just go for the prata

Was waiting for my order when I saw a family doing hand signs to figure out what to order. The cashier came out immediately to take their orders along the walkway while trying his best to do sign language. The food is great and the service has‚Ä¶compassion.
Egg prata is really thick and nice...the curry is also not too watery and yummyüòã
One of the best family Chinese food restaurants I visited in Singapore the decor is simple but the food is excellent in service was great

Had dinner with family at Northpoint outlet. Very impressed by the service of ÈùôÈõ™ and Xiaoli. They were very cheerful and attentive to our needs. Took initiative to offer fruits and freebies and plated out the birthday cake which we bought. The team even sang song for us and prepared a hat made from balloons. After that, they helped us pack the leftovers nicely. Best service and comparable to Êµ∑Â∫ïÊçû...

content: Gem at west area. Only disappointing dish is that the spinach is watery and diluted. Service is not very good because they make u wait. Ordered masala tea and recheck with one of the staff but seem to ignore us. However the masala tea is very good!! Mutton murtabak has alot filling too

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: 45dollar 1 pot... Nice and wine X. O HOT POT VRY WORTH

content: Rice was fragrant. But the grilled chicken was disappointing, its was tasteless and mushy (totally different from tender). Its like lifeless meat. Chilli wasnt what i expected too, there is a weird taste lingering in the mouth.

Great food at great value!
Attended a wine pairing dinner, superb!

Cozy place for gathering with friends and family.

Surprisingly the skewers tasted quite good, although the price is slightly expensive than those Japanese food you can found in town like orchard area.

Best to go if you‚Äôre looking for job-crowded place for lunch. Definitely can give a try if you‚Äôre looking for beers and wine at night. üå∏üå∏

Expensive price for poor quality of food. Nasi goreng thai only 1pcs small prawn, nasi not cook consistently white rice can still be seen. Drinks haphazard, skimped on ingredients, drinking diluted teh chino....
Waiting for 2 hours and food is cold, pls don‚Äôt come to this place
Super value and delicious. Fresh ingredients, thin Al dente ramen with good, non MSG soup :)

Good Thai Food in Toa Payoh. Good prices. Be prepared to queue and wait for your food. Parking is a limited because it's for season parking. Aside from that, enjoyed the food especially the Green Curry Chicken! üëçüëçüëç

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Food quantity is good, sauces are nice and friendly staff

Staffs are prompted and courteous

Whenever am here during weekend, always see a super long Q for this stall but didn't get to try it till last weekend though there's still about 10 person in front but at least given that only 2 pax dine-in, thus waiting time is not as bad.

Loved how they are generous with the lard and fried shallots. Loved their fish cake and fish ball too as you don't get to taste lots of flour but more of the fish paste.

Coffee shop area also quite traditional with those antique kind of marble table with wooden legs and wooden round chairs.

Will definitely come back again if the Q is not that long or if I"m able to wake up super duper early for this (maybe when I got the craving). Lolxxx
Wide variety of food here
Wait staff was very friendly. Chicken was tender, and the chicken rice was flavorful while not greasy.

Outlet in Compass One with no chicken left after 730pm. Poor Business ethics and failure to provide enough number of chickens to serve customers. Wondering if customers buy chicken is like Singapore is undergoing another Circuit Breaker or end of the world. Else the outlet will only sell chicken rice at SGD$100 or One whole chicken at SGD$1000. I can't believe that the outlet does not even have chicken drumstick rice which I wanted to buy for my three year old for her dinner.
Do avoid Compass One outlet by all means if you do not want to leave Boon Tong Kee empty handed or you do not want to get deceived by price in Menu.

Went to the Winstedt outlet. The service don't even deserve 1 star. Very bad experience. Went to celebrate a family member's birthday but ended up waiting 2 hours before we finally got our food. Very disappointed.  The restaurant had a birthday celebration going on, so we would've understood a slight delay in preparing our orders. But the restaurant paid more attention in preparing food for the birthday event with little regard for the other paying customers. We saw more than 20 customers cancelling their orders due to the super long waiting time. The restaurant could have been better organised... or dedicate different sections of the kitchen to cater to the different types of customers (i.e. event booking and walk-in). Service sucks.
A pleasant find at Toa Payoh. Juicy, succulent and well seasoned chicken chop. The charred garlic bits gave crunch and punch to the aglio olio. Excellent value for the quality.

Very slow service. Ordered at 12.30pm and got order by 1.10pm! Waited so long took my whole lunch hours.

Update: the food is quite nice and tasty! Generous servings. Only the cooking time can be improved. üëçüèº

Lunch crowd filled this small eatery. Food is good but as its crowded, service would need some improvement
Quite authentic Thai food. It‚Äôs also affordable.
But at this industrial area, go if you are around the corner
Rendang beef is very delicious. The rice is also very fragrant.

My 2nd time eating Korean Chinese restaurant. Would say this place is the best value for $$. Ban Chan is good especially the Kimchi. Best dish of the day is the Tangsuyuk followed by Jjajangmyeon and Jjamppong.
For Tangsuyuk, the sauce and meat is better than the 1st. Jjajangmyeon the 1st is better but the onions in the sauce is more. Jjamppong tasted average. Ordered a set C for a young family of 4 is just right.
Maybe we got in on a bad day. Beef brisket was too chewy. Chicken was undercooked at some parts. Kitchen seemed a understaffed. Pasta was simple and great though.
Price increased $1 per steak 5 July 2021
Very good

Fried rice has no taste. Better go to wok hey.

Mince meat noodle is too salty. Hair will surely drop.

Pan fried bun.. overpriced, over hyped. Doesn't taste like much.

Didn't finish my food. And I'm not even particular about food.

Tons of foods to choose from. Tried most of the food here and my favourites include char kway teow, prawn noodles and kway chap!

Nicer than some authentic malaysian food that i've had in different parts of malaysia.
Ruined my expectations of hawker western food. BECAUSE ITS SO GOOD

Third time here and it just gets better with each visit.
You have to order the grilled pork. One of the few and best I've had in sg.

(Translated by Google) 2017.4.22 Revisited
I visited again last dinner because it was very delicious, the atmosphere was good and the appetizers and soup had particularly delicate tastes so I visited again. As always, delicious appetizer and shark fin soup. Other fish dishes and mapo beans were eaten, but they were too spicy to be honest. People who like spicy foods will surely be delicious. The small basket parcel was delicious, and the dessert mango pudding was delicious with a novel texture. Lunch course is $ 48 per person. It is always recommended for some reason.

Very delicious and good atmosphere and service. We had a fish course, but everything was delicious.

Kampong chicken and duck looked and tasted overnight. All the other dishes below par. Any normal zi char outside is better. Will probably not go back there again. Actually the worst i have been to.

Pro: Super friendly staffs.
Con: The food really can't make the cut.
Food is really not bad just that the staffs lacks EQ and abit rude. If you don't mind service and just want some food, this could be a possible choice
Conveniently located, so accessible with fuss-free parking, not so crowded setting, best of all consistent comfort "chicken rice" food!

We wished to bring your attention that with many years of patronage and good dinning experiences has gone to the drains.
Recently we had experienced ( many times) very rude counter staffs that were not trained in service sectors. This incidents have caused major upsets.
Hope that this bunch of jokers be replaced asap to avoid further degradation and damage to your good establishment.
Thanks
Danny Ng

Decent bowl of prawn noodle at $3.50 with generous servings of ingredients.  Includes 2 good size prawn and love the pork lard generously spread among the noodle.  Soup could be more robust but otherwise can‚Äôt really complain at this price point.
Food is reasonably tasty but the portions here tend to be rather small. It is also quite far away from my house.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: This mookata is quite obscure unless you're familiar with the neighbourhood. Once I was there, it was not obvious that there was a waiting line unless you ask the staff and the wait was quite long almost an hour. The wait was worth it as the food was really flavourful. There is a hawker beside which you can fuel up a little while waiting too. There were 5 of us and each of us paid about $10 excluding the drinks which was a really good deal. Not a lot of drinks selection though.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: One of the good Nasi Padang in S‚Äôpore. They only serve lamb Rendang on Friday. Live the way they flavoured and spiced the meats. Vegetables are cooked just right. Long queue during peak hours. Lastly, very affordable!
Power
Nice food

Used to go once every couple of weeks because that claypot chicken + omelette combo is like no other. Testament to the food and chef that the restaurant is still going strong after nearly two decades in the corner of a nondescript building. It gets packed.
Yummy food. There is always a queue for this. Surprisingly, the food comes very quickly so the wait isn't that long. I love the taste of the jiaozi.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Very worst food in North Point mall. I went there eat some food all spoiled and very oily.
Chun Rong has been an exemplary staff, friendly, attentive and Knowledgeble of the food. The lobster is great. Will be back for the duck
Its actually very Under rated.. I love it. The sambal kway teow is very nice! I wanna try the kway chap one day!
Pork belly is nicely grilled and tasty, but a little confused why there was kimchi in Japanese bowl. Tasted a little like homemade food.

The food in this restaurant was expensive. We (5 adults) ordered 6 dishes all medium portion and cost us $113.60 which equate to $22 per pax. The half salt chicken was too dry, yong tau foo soup, abacus yam and fermented prawn so so only. Only The vege was nice and mei chai pork belly not salty but okay. If u are not a hakka, please turn back.

If you like old school Chinese dumplings but don‚Äôt want to Din Tai Feng, there is always Jing Hua. The shop is well known for its so-called Chinese pizza (‰∏âÈ≤úÁõíÂ≠ê). However, I would like to recommend that you try the pan fried dumplings (‰∏âÈ≤úÈîÖË¥¥). You can see both in the pictures below. They also have a lot of frozen dumplings available for take-away, which is quite popular here. Of course they also have many of the usual suspects, but why not try something different? Service is fine and the price is reasonable. My only gripe would be that they do the usual Chinese restaurant scammy thing and charge for wet towels. To be fair, they‚Äôre probably more like 3.5 stars that four, but I‚Äôm not willing to round down to three here. The dumplings are pretty tasty and satisfying.
Waitress was prompt and attentive, cashier was kind to advise on the current promotion for enjoying the discount. Dining experience is  awesome!

Overall a disappointment. Though the fried rice was fragrance but the rice were way too meshy, probably an off day for them but I can only rate what was served.

I also decided to add a squid cutlet to the fried rice instead of the usual chicken/pork cutlet but it was pathetically bite size yet cost much more than if ordering the chicken/pork cutlet fried rice combo.

2nd visit:
A much improvement over the 1st visit, maybe cos I have it on site this time. Also only after the meal then I realised they actually have an indoor dining area which is hard to notice cos the kitchen is right in the middle between the indoor and outdoor seating.

Didn't managed to capture all the dishes that were ordered. the crab omelette is really good! A must try! Overall most of the dishes were pretty yummy and portion was good for 5! We ordered 3 rice/noodles, a meat and a side. Big eaters might want to order a little more! The ambience was nice and we saw that the menu has sashimi and oysters as well hence it's more a fusion restaurant. Friendly staff and service!

Tasty and decent pricing.
Sweet and sour pork rice was too sweet, but the Mee goreng was good!
Accepts cash, nets and Amex.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Wonderful Bar restaurant good food good place to hang out with friends
Everytime order from foodpanda, restaurant will cancel order. Encountered so many time.

This prawn mee remind me of my childhood. At Malaysia, KL, Jalan cheras, there is one prawn mee stall at the road side. I have always missed this taste.

The soup is very rich, tasty and flavourful. Is very different from the Singapore taste.  Strongly recommend to give it a try if you are around there.
Food is good but service not so good due to lack of staff @ time of visit around 10 a.m.,

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Cheap and authentic taste. Can't find any place cheaper than this!

Was excited to see Shanghai pan fried buns! However we left that place disappointed.

Shanghai buns were oily and skin was too think and doughy.

Xiao loong baos had thick skin and oily inside probably due to the fatty meat used.

Tried the dry minced meat noodles and was doused in oil too.

Tried the sour soup wasn‚Äôt great and should be served piping hot which wasn‚Äôt.

Service was no frills but fast. And for the price we paid, 28 bucks is rather cheap. Guess you pay for what you get.

Visited on a Sat for dinner. Ordering is done via the QR code. Had the pork bowl, Australian wagyu bowl & salmon sashimi. The pork was very tender with a rich flavour from the marinade. Beef was way too tough and not worth it. 10/10 would not order again as there are better places for beef. Service is pleasant.

One of the paradise group restaurants that never fails to deliver good food and services.

It‚Äôs usually crowded during dinner time especially weekends so do expect estimate of 30 minutes waiting time.

Food came relatively quick after ordering.
Beef noodle - it‚Äôs surprisingly good on both the noodle and meat! Would even be better if the portion is slightly bigger.
Ting Zai congee - one of the signature dish and its tasty even without soy sauce.
XO carrot cake - soft and fragrant
Liu Sa Bao - nicely presented though it seems to downsize a little
Spicy vinegar dumplings - well filled on the ingredients

If you were to go during weekday 3 - 5pm, there is an ongoing tea time promotion with up to 40% discount. If not otherwise it may be slightly pricey.
Fish and chips batter is very good and big portion

Cheap seafood zi car place, you can‚Äôt ask for more these days. We had 16 pax with 8 dishes for 2 tables, only costs us $306. Really value for money.

Price - great!
Ambiance- can get a little stuffy since there‚Äôs is no aircond
Food - great!
Staff - easy going although they were super busy, they were not rude.
Location - good

We had
Pork meat bun - signature must try!
Curry fish head - Nyonya style, not Asam style, still good!
Herbal prawn in claypot - love it! Fresh prawn and legit herbal soup
Not bad, but taste not heavy compare to malaysia thai

waited 15mins for my order. asked staff A about it and he replied ok. another 15mins passed i asked staff B and he said ok too. after another 15mins i went to ask staff C and when he checked, the order was not even taken?!?! no communication between staff

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Queuing system sucks. Call and ask but we aren't allowed to make reservation. Waiting outside the store for more than 45 mins. They should have a queuing system to get a queue number. No air con no chair at the waiting area. A waste of time.
Ordered the Signature Yakiniku-GO Set full steak with 3 types of cuts and Wagyu beef set.  The only complaint is they limit to 50 minutes for the dining-in.
My favourite place to fulfill my craving on authentic singaporean Curry Puffs.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Awesome food, my personal favourite was the butter chicken masala. Sometimes it gets crowded at morning and evenings because of it's popularity.

I didn't visit this restaurant since they moved to Airview Building about 3 years ago. The place was clean and spacious for a Dim Sum Cantonese restaurant. Service staff were attentive and friendly. The standard of the food is still good. We ordered to much this time but still happy with it. The siew mai is a very traditional way of making siew mai. Very fresh and juicy. The beancurd roll with prawns was very crispy, light and tasty. Too tempting. Forgot to take a photo before eating. The crispy noodles with seafood was great. Not oily at all. Spinach in superior broth was ok. Loved the homemade tofu with mushroom. Peking duck was ok. They wrapped it for you so by the time you eat it, it's not as crispy as it should have been.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Fantastic service and value for $$ delicious food. I love the sauces
Very tasty, food well presented. Price wise very economical! Thumbs up for the service! ‚ù§Ô∏è

The Couple is friendly and nice. The food is average in comparison as they are many good Thai food in Singapore. The portion is not big as stated. The portion is just right. I don't consider cheap there are restaurants in Singapore who serve cheaper and equal quality Thaifood Nahkron, Nangfa, Soi 47, Just Thai with better environment . But still will support as I stayed around that area.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
Second visit here and still tastes good!
We enjoyed every dish we had and will be back to try other dishes!

The chicken wing is yummy and the curry fish was great too!

Previously I ordered steamed meat with salted fish and it was enjoyable.

Parking may be a bit challenging.
The prata is crispy and made fresh when you order. Great selection of prata but the tea  halia and mango lassi is disappointing.

We love the food here! Taste is awesome, presentation is unique, and we really enjoyed our meal every time we are here. we highly recommend the mermaid (fish dish in collagen soup), flaming pineapple, truffle hor fun, and the hanging bacon salad! Great place for family meal and presentable for bringing guests.

A new find for the family and what a surprise find! Delicious fresh Authentic food @ affordable prices. Dishes to try include the steamboat, har cheong Kai, prawn rolls fried pork! They may be opening a stall soon in Aljunied so hit them up there as well.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Great taste , took it for my wife confinement .. she really loves it , even me also used yo taste and love it !

Knew the uncle since i was a boy. till today if walk pass his shop pakcik will ask "have you eaten"? When i was a boy pakcik always gave free food to us. Very kind and generous pakcik. Food price is really cheap $1 nasi lemak and $4 for nasi sambal goreng with chicken and lastly the taste of the food never change since the first time i ate it. Its simply delicious!!

The standard of food here is simply unacceptable. I‚Äôve been here multiple times in the morning, each time with the ludicrous hope that it will be better than the previous time. The porridge is so watery it feels like you‚Äôre drinking salted rice water. There were literally only 1.5 pieces of chicken in my bowl, which itself was only 2/3 full. I have never had such an atrocious experience in other KFCs before - please close this outlet down as it is a disgrace to the brand name.
doesn‚Äôt listen when asked for no olives takes forever quite long but the food edible so i eat :)

u better ramp up order management...got high tech ordering tags still can forget it order for more den 30 mins take away...written down but mind went blank..how nice it is ,we won't be patronising  again

Mee Hoon Kuey Stall
The super super bad experience in my life. The staff can't speak properly in both languages, mandarin and English. Just anyhow shouting, the diners all don't know the food is for who. Super super bad queues management. Not in system. The diners can anyhow take other person order. PLEASE TAKE NOTE train ur staff properly. Don't spoil Malaysia standard.

Decided to try this place out, and I must say I've been pleasantly surprised. Ordered the veggie meal and it was fantastic. They go easy on the salt, keeping the taste homely and grounded. Good variety of veggies. Good portions. Liked the rasam and the pickle. Loved the presentation with clay utensils (incl. the water jug). Was about to order ginger tea and they recommended an off-menu item, Masala tea (Must try, just request them to use milk rather than the usual for a rich, milky texture). Place has a wonderful, homely atmosphere. A quiet ambience. Staff was extremely courteous and polite, including a very passionate owner. The menu is authentic South Indian cuisine based, with dishes I hadn't even heard of.
If you wanna have a good, off-the-beat, authentic South Indian experience, give this place a try.

Not very crowded when we were there on a Sunday afternoon.

Ice milo is $3.60 a cup! I thought that was a bit too expensive for a coffee shop setting.

Food is generally nice. The garlic chicken was not to my liking as they cooked with curry powder. Stir fry la la is very nice. The sauce is good. Claypot rice is generous with the salted fish.

I ordered seafood fried rice but it was super disappointing. It costs $15 but looks so poor in terms of ingredients. I probably could get better seafood fried rice at any hawker center less than $5. Please do not order seafood fried rice.
Reasonable price and tasty food!Addicted to their meal and whenever we feel like eating western they are the first thing comes to our mind.Thank you for providing a delicious food brothers.

Spring chicken was very good, my children and my favourite. The skin is crispy and meat is juicy... like the fresh vege at the side. Tried a few times and the consistency is there.
Sunday night crowd comes in around 630pm... Good to come slightly earlier if there's young kids to feed.

This post i am writing after experiencing it  after many times.Highly disappointing. food quality is so bad. Attached is the photo of  the packing  provided for takeaway... So finger licking good it is.

Established in June 2001 as part of the Amara Singapore hotel's restaurants, Silk Road Restaurant serves culinary delights inspired by the historic trade route through China.
.
Ambience at Silk Road Restaurant has an understated Oriental elegance, refined yet quiet, suitable for business gatherings.
.
The spacious dining hall is spot lit, the light over each table lending sufficient illumination, while thoughtfully arranged comfortable furnishings and use of shadows create a sense of privacy for each table.
.
Service at Silk Road Restaurant is attentive and friendly. As there usually aren't that many diners here, staff can afford to devote time and care to guests, proactively refilling water and tea, and offering to clear finished plates throughout the meal.
.
Food at Silk Road Restaurant highlights Chinese Mandarin cuisine, spanning the regions of Sichuan, Beijing, Shanghai, and Shaanxi.
.
Dishes are well-executed with above average quality, making for a decent meal. Dumplings are a highlight here, with several different options.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Tried it as Lin Chi Lin is their ambassador. It is super comforting to combat my fatigue and provides me with a high nutritional value without the bad thing. It tastes better with traditional chicken essence. I always pour one bag in my cooked mee suah as quick light meal fix. My life saver during my morning sickness period.

This is almost the best mookata I have ever had!
Food is fresh, marination is awesome, service is great and most important thing is chilli ‰∏ÄÁ∫ßÊ£í!
Their boss only serve the best quality of food!
And I have to say their staff super friendly!
What‚Äôs most important?
The bill is super pocket friendly also.
This is a must try and to die for mookata!

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Love the chicken essence taste. Unlike other brand that I tried before gt a weird chicken taste. This taste exactly like double boiled chicken soup. Highly recommended it. ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è
Food not bad a bit expensive but worth to try it.
Amazing food

Place was literally empty at 5pm and i found out why.

You order from your own phone, had difficulty ordering due to some bugs. Almost wanted to leave after 3 failed attempts. They copied Genki Sushi delivery by train which is a gimmick.

Food took sometime to come, powdered green tea is awful. These has got to be the smallest pieces of sushi i've gotten from a restaurant and the takoyaki has the size of small fishballs came cold and hard.

I would skip this joint for better variety and quality at sushi express.
Great steak and curly fries!

Value for $ deal, 2 x Unagi for $18.

Taste wise pretty ok, rice was ok. The Unagi lacked the sauce the gives the flavor but nonetheless it wasn't dry and meat was tender.
Very fine touches make even normal sounding dishes sing. Paired with great service it is a Michelin starred restaurant waiting to be awarded.

The focus is on no pork dishes

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: This is a hidden gem! Amazing food. Good service. Great food and the owner is an amazing lady. The prices are so reasonable. They also serve beer and wine. They serve North Indian, South Indian and Indian Chinese. Overall a great find. They have survived the pandemic and even expanded to an adjacent unit. Speaks volumes of their resilience and determination.
Rude workers. Oily food. Overpriced definitely.

Tucked away in a corner on the second floor of the building. Not a big space but a wide menu of Teochew and Hainanese Food. What we ordered was delicious. The lady serving us was super friendly. Thumbs up!

This is our first visit in almost 2 years. What surprise us pleasantly was how their service has become more personable.  All the waitresses and managers always have a smile on their face when they approached our table and speak to our children. I have not had such a feeling for a long time and for a while gave up being served.  At the end of the day, there is restaurants with great food and limited service and there is restaurant with decent food with great service. I will certainly choose the latter.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Aston‚Äôs/Andes has always been a go-to place for good food at decent prices. However during my latest visit, I was made to queue for over 45 mins despite the restaurant being less than half full. Already quite annoyed, when I was finally seated at a table, I noticed that people who were at the front of the queue when I reached the place were already leaving, that‚Äôs how long the wait was. Food didn‚Äôt come for another 20-30 mins and when it did, the portion of food was disgustingly small and the wellness of the steak was nowhere close to the requested. Overall an overwhelmingly disappointing experience and very frustrating in terms of service.
So-so food but service was good

Update: FB page owner had informed me that he had sold to new owner. He got new owner to call me and refunded the cost. Amended from 1 star to 3 star.

Be warned if you are eating there for the first time! Super sweet like hell drinks and dishonest business with super long queue wth service preference going towards eat in and same skin colour.

I ordered face to face at counter yesterday for takeaway with the following food.
2 garlic naans
2 plain means
1 chicken tika
1 panner tika masala
2 hot tea
Paid $20 worth of CDC vouchers and $4.40 cash

The drinks are so sweet that one can be an instant diabetic upon first mouthful.

As for the food, I only got 4 naans and 1 chickpea curry instead?!?!?

Avoid at all cost.

Ordered char-siu spicy miso ramen at S$9.50.

The broth tasted good and the ramen texture was Q enough.  It was not spicy but was acceptable.  It would have been better if the char-siu was tender / succulent.

Both the staff were very friendly and have good customer service.

Will return for other ramen :)

Perfectly crispy fries and great service.

However the steak was chewy and more medium-well than medium-rare, and the mac and cheese just didn't taste good.

Nachos were bland, but the roast pork it came with was tasty. They don't really go well together though, it's not like they can be eaten together...

All in all would only come back for the fries.

Good food & good service.
Salted egg prawn: 5/5. SGD21.5 without GST. Only 6pcs. However, the prawn are big and fresh!
Sweet and sour pork: 5/5. Best sweet and sour pork in Singapore.
Tofu salt pepper: 2/5. So so...
A family favourite for its delicious Zhi-Char dishes and efficient service by staff, you can bet we‚Äôd be back for more ü•∞

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Yummy and tasty set meal for lunch. Worth every dollar spent üëåüèªüòä
The food is served quickly and is piping hot. Really love the tomato cashew sauce - it‚Äôs a must try!

Great tasting food at affordable pricing, they give huge servings too!
Open 24/7 but certain items are not available at midnight.
Very nice ambience. Good food and reasonable price. Will come back again.
Good food
We ordered the set dinner for two... None of the dishes disappointed us... All were good and very rich in flavour... Overall a great meal...

Portion became smaller. Ordered chix cutlet rice. Few pieces of chicken on white rice.

Ordered 3 chicken wings. Overcooked with black patches.

I ordered before another lady. End up lady got the order before me.

Went to ask the cashier a male, how come take so long. Give me theory lesson that fried chicken wings takes longer to cook than fried fish.

Wow. Lor wonder my 3 pieces chicken wings was overcooked n had random black patches

Thanks not coming back. Service sucks like the food.

Those ordering from grab, its the same male chef cooking your sometimes under or overcooked fish/chicken. If a chef cant be consistent what he puts out, wonder how he survive so long.
Been told by the staff waiting time half an hour but ended up become one hour waiting time. It is better to order first at home then come and collect. Don‚Äôt waste one hour to waiting here .

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Went on a Friday afternoon for lunch, was crowded. We order our usual dishes. Food was not bad but the rice lack the fragrance which it used to have. Something might be missing. Surprisingly, other outlets rice tasted differently from this particular Thomson outlet. Hopefully, the rice can be improved.

Authentic Shanghainess dishes. Must try... shanghai Xiao long bao, Sheng Jian bao and the Popiah ( abit oily). Dishes portion not big we ordered 10 dishes, just right for 3 adults, 1 teenager and a kid. Recommend to make reservation as the place is not big.
Staff are fantastic. Easter to assist and make sure you are happy. Great menu.

Ambience was good.  Ordered 4 dishes for a family of 3.  Prawn pancake and the hor fun were good but have to eat it while it is hot.  Poarched chicken was normal and egg plant was too oily.  Overall rating was above normal.  Price a little steep.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Very good nasi lemak and fast take out delivery service too. üëçüëçüëç

The mala here is definitely one of the best and cheaper ones I have had.

They offer ingredients that one would normally not find in other mala stalls but still manage to blend them seamlessly into the dish. I would highly recommend the eggs, which they serve scrambled on top of the dish. Another unique point would be how they deep-fry certain ingredients (best of which are the potatoes, lotus root, and fish) which add an extra layer of texture and taste. I find the dry version to be the better style of their mala, but this is not to discount the soup version, which is rather flavourful as well. Though do expect to wait around 15 - 25 minutes, which feels rather acceptable to me considering the level of preparation.

The price is based off the weight of the ingredients, irregardless of whether they are meat or vegetable. Compared to other mala stalls, the price here is considerably cheaper and you can expect to spend around S$8 - 10 per person for a filling portion.

The store has a great ambience as well with a cozy indoor setting and also a cool outdoor seating overlooking a part of the campus. Some seats to wait at is also provided along the corridor to the store which is an added bonus.

I end with their service, which is mainly what prompted me to write this review. The staff there have always been friendly and helpful in all my visits. I would like to highlight a recent visit when they unfortunately made a mistake in the order. As we only noticed later when the store was about to close, we were not able to ask for the missing ingredients. However, my friend was contacted by an employee of the store who was very apologetic and offered a discount off our next order. The responsibility and service shown by the staff through this action definitely reinforced the consistency in their service.

All in all, definitely worth the trip into NTU!

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Good to have an Indian restaurant in Ang Mo Kio with air-conditioning. Looking forward to have more great Indian food. Had quick lunch today, love the food. Unfortunately, didn't take a photo.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Good place for a vibe. Nice food at reasonable price. Service is good as well. Ice plant and charcoal tofu is a must to order.

We came here after seeing Daniel Food Diary‚Äôs review (though we know to take all the bloggers‚Äô reviews with a big pinch of salt).

In a nutshell, the food here is decent. Just skip the desserts and the coffee (which is a collaboration with local Hook coffee but the cafe does not have a barista in house). After lunch, simply hop over to Thus Coffee which is just around the corner.

It‚Äôs nice, quiet and spacious spot for catching up over lunch. On a Monday noon, it wasn‚Äôt crowded at all. We had a nice far end spot where behind the doors is the backyard with a water well.

We ordered the otah bruschetta (sourdough), seafood aglio olio, fishy business (salmon), roffles platter and wild mushroom risotto. All of us rather enjoyed our respective main course.

Thereafter, we shared the ondeh ondeh cake, yuzu cheesecake and a warm apple crumble and also had cups of coffee.

The Apple crumble looked really funky and unnatural (take a look at the last photo) plus it was too sweet. The ondeh ondeh was nothing to rave about either. Coffee was served without inspiration (no latte art cos as mentioned, no barista) - it was just bland, normal coffee but at a barista price tag of $7.

Ordered their chicken wings with waiting for our dinner to arrive. Their chicken wings were very tasty and crispy. Priced at $1.50 per piece with a minimums order of 2pcs. Their menu looks good and I hope to come by to try more of your dishes soon.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Had Mother‚Äôs Day dinner at the place, took up the set dinner for ease due to large number. Generally food was decent but nothing to rave about. Costs about $40-$50/pax for the set. ‚Ä¶

Beef Steak (SGD $14 / $25) @ Jack's Place.
.
Founded in 1966 by Jack Hunt and subsequently expanded by Say Lip Hai from 1974 onwards, this old-time casual steakhouse was once ridiculed for selling 'up-market' Western fare in heartland HDB locations.
.
Seniors may well recall those times in the early 1980s, when a set meal here - consisting of a soup, sirloin steak, salad, baked potato, fruit cocktail, and coffee/tea, cost just SGD $5.20..... at a time when a typical meal was less than SGD $2.
.
These days, their steaks remain as good as before, grilled to your requested doneness, served sizzling on a hot plate. The beef ribeye is juicy and tender, with a satisfying light chew, and robust meaty savoury salty flavour.
.
The accompanying boiled vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, carrot) have bright vegetal sweet flavour, while the soft baked potato with starchy sweet notes has old-school toppings served tableside - rich sour cream, crisp spring onions, chewy bacon bits. Filling.
.
They also specialise in the tenderloin cut, with 1 option being an eye-catching tableside flambe.
All is good, ambience and food, the only things that put off is the incense that smell horrible
Decent steak in a cozy coffee shop. Good location with ample parking space and a friendly boss who always seems so happy and positive.
