Ordered the beef curry and the fried chicken on grab. The food was ok at best and the rice was a bit too wet and mushy for my liking. Would prefer for them to separate the curry from the rice so the rice won‚Äôt soak up the curry.

Had A Quick Lunch @ Newly Opened Sushi-Go. Waiting Time Wasnt Long . A Robot Ushered Me To My Seat. Scan & Order Via QR Code. Staffs Over There Were Friendly & Welcoming Too. Those Diff Emoji Faces Of Go-Bots Delivered My Food Looked So Cute Plus Efficient. The Sushi And Fried Stuffs Taste Great Too. Hope To See More Dessert Choices In Future Like Sushi Express. Spend Abt $19, Pretty Affordable. Located Near TimeZone/ Cinema, 4th Level.

(Translated by Google) Friendly service, yummy padang rice

(Original)
Friendly service, yummy nasi padang

I always enjoyed Indian food.  The chapatti is nice and the gravy is generous.  The chapatti is rather small but they have 4 pcs. Still,  I had bigger chapatti at about the same price they charge.
Will return to try other goodies though.
Always my fav place for crab bee hoon and sliced fish soup. Love this cosy HK restaurant. Expect crowd during lunch and dinner. Do make reservation if you are going in group

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Great Roast Foodie

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Order through delivery platform, cost $25.90. Portion for 2 pax. With no rice included.
Extremely slow service, food took over 30 mins to come, food quality sub par. Staff rude and restaurant is unable to handle a crowd. Will not recommend to others.
Unpretentious japanese grill stall. With just 5 seats, waiting time could be long so avoid meals time. Ordered premium steak don. Beef is well marinated but egg could be a bit runnier. No miso soup.

First time here, ate the claypot chicken rice
5/5 for me... Reasonable portion and value for the current market trend.
Food was quick and very delicious.

Also tasted abit of the fried kway teow, it was also very delicious.

Looking forward to trying other dishes in the future. üëçüôè.
A famous spot in the neighbours qorth traveling for

Excited with the idea of being able to explore Springleaf with the new MRT Brown line, I headed over to Springleaf Prata Place to try their paper thosai and cheese prata. We ordered our drinks, Kopi ice and Teh ice, and were surprisingly pleased by it. They were perfect, unlike what the other reviews might imply. Here's a tip : If the drink has bubbles on top, it's probably good :)

My partner had her Mozz.Cheese prata and it was jampackedddd with cheese, better than any other places I can think of in Singapore. Curry was thick but not spicy, so I guess there's a negative there.

So far, if my experience had ended here, I'd give this place a 5/5. Then I had a bite of my paper thosai.

Thosai was crispy, but only because the thin parts were burnt and bitter! Thicker areas as so thick because the batter was scrapped off. The mouth feel was practically too chewy like gum or too crumbly like sand!

To make it worse, the dhaal and chutney was especially thin and flavourless. Spent so much time scrapping the bottom to pick up more bits within the watery gravy, I felt like I was fishing üé£üé£üé£üé£ üêüüêüüêü

In spite of this, I admit lah, maybe their batter wasn't good that day or they had a bad day in the kitchen. Still, to this day, the worst thosai I've had and I've had a lott of thosai. My tastebuds were disappointed and hurt, even their plaster prata cannot cover my disappointment.

TLDR: Come here for their prata and their prata only.

Ordered a steam fish Mala soup and a Ala Carte with multiple ingredient with medium spiciness! Really nice!
The taste is strong and flavourful but less fragrant as compared to the Mala store at NEX food court and Central food court. But still good and value for money.
Food was great...but I really dislike the ambience and the music.

I had the fried pork Noodle. The broth was delicious and there was a good amount ingredients in the dish. However, there were parts of the noodles which were clumped together and was undercooked and inedible. The fried pork that came with the dish although was cooked and tasted good, had slices which were just the fats.

We had a great evening here. Nice food, great ambience. The service is good, staffs are patient and attentive. I like the tender and juicy pork cheek, crispy fish skin! My friends like their spicy Sichuan chicken... thought I requested less spicy, but it still very spicy to me. Btw, it's supposed to taste spicy üòÖ so beware if you can't take spicy food. Hmm... feedback, the chicken is not crispy enough. Nothing to shout about on their Crabmeat Ee-fu noodles.
Hmm...Escape to Keifeng is good.

I Love Colourful NOVENA. I spend most of my daily time at Novena & Newton Area since July 2016. Novena & Newton consider my 2nd home place which I just love my work as salesperson. Wishing everyone to have a dream home at Novena & Newton area. Do engage me if like to know more about Novena & Newton.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Authentic Hunan food and taste is great. Cash or nets payment only but no GST
Theva and team provided excellent service with their pleasant approach! :) kuddos to the team in Safra Toa Payoh! You guys deserve recognition for all your hard work.

Poor environment. The restaurant did not control what kind of liquor that the customers bring in. And allow the customers to drunk and make a lot of loud noises. Affecting the rest of the customers. The manager did not even do the job by controlling. This restaurant is poor to have your fine dining here. Look elsewhere if you want to have a good dinner.

First time customer. Very polite and efficient staff. Food was tasty (chicken!!) and I like the neat condiments set up.
Only issue is the aircon. Almost can‚Äôt feel any aircon. Otherwise, everything is good. Thank you.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Taste downgraded from 1-2 years ago. The Basil Pork looked really bland and tasted like economic rice standard. Lastly is this woman stationed at the counter who always seem hesitant to serve customers
Nice food. Portion for set meal is way too big though..
Generous servings and good service. The side dishes are delicious and also the sweet & sour pork

if I had given a review months ago when they first opened I would probably have given 4  stars . I actually thought they were ok , pretty decent , other then salmon skin which arrived cold and rather oily . Average reviews were over 4 stars then .

Visited yesterday and was stunned by the drastic drop in standards.
The salmon sashimi was literally pink like it's dried for a while .  My company thought it was weird for me to recommend genki since he boycotted for a while due to low standards.  And after seeing the salmon I just couldn't bring myself to send in the rest of the orders.

They also got our orders wrong.
It wasn't busy yet it happened.  So I have no idea what's happening in the kitchen .
When we received the tuna roll they actually felt warm to the mouth.  This is an air conditioned restaurant and something with raw fish felt warmer than room temperature.

Unless things change I doubt I'll be adventurous enough to risk another experience here .
There was some sort of plastic ap in my takeaway claypot rice. I almost choked on it. I think my rice had melted plastic inside. Only realise this after I ate half of it

Value-for-money Quick-Lunch menu, Hainanese Pork Chop rice at $6 nett. The pork was tender and lean, with good portion size for the price. Sauce was a bit too sweet for me. Plus points for the friendly service and clean environment.

Enjoyed our lunch here. We will return to try other dishes :) the mentai salmon was aburi even though it wasn‚Äôt stated but all‚Äôs good, it was still yummy! The place is abit quiet when we were there so no issues finding a seat :)
Like their food
Steak is very good ! Ok

The food here tastes really good and authentic. The Pad Thai is really delicious. The Basil Pork is moist and has a lot of flavour. The Grilled Pork has a ton of flavour and when you dip in the chili fish sauce that you can ask for, it is absolutely fabulous. I have went there at least 5 times and it never gets worse.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Ordered prata as I thought the preparation won't take long. However, got to know that they were cleaning the kitchen, which I thought was fair enough, at least they're keeping the place clean. But I don't like the idea of the person cleaning the kitchen to handle the food afterwards. Had to cancel the whole order after waiting for 20 minutes due to the "kitchen cleaning". But one of the staff did apologise and refunded the full amount though.

Very generous food portions and personable service. I enjoyed the smoked duck pasta a lot - rich strong flavours that dance in your mouth. And I had a nice big chocolate shake (not pictured) to wash it all down.

Sunday night dinner at this quaint little restaurant with just a few tables - called last minute and wasnt able to get a table initially but the owner called back to say someone cancelled üòÖ lucky haha

Food was pretty good: pork chop noodles were decent but the flavour lacked depth. The chicken and mushrooms noodles were better with the taste of ginger cutting through the sweetness of the mushroom and soy sauce. The cold drunken chicken was yummy and tender while the xiaolongbao‚Äôs soup was very flavorful!

All in all pretty decent food, price in the mid ranges at $68 for 4 people

Staff was friendly, price is affordable. I ordered their soup of the day (tomato) and F4. Pan Seared fish with Cafe de Paris Butter. The wait wasn't long and the food was fresh and flavorful. Would recommend.
Great food and drink. Some of the best service we‚Äôve ever had in Singapore and our favorite maki rolls yet.

All the dishes are delicious, the best should be the steamed fish.
For those who're vegetarians they will separately serve if you gathered within same table
The teriyaki chicken don and unagi don are the more popular items here.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Yesterday's Fish Noodle Soup was a bit saltier but still taste good with added cooking wine.
Not good, feel they discriminate locals
Extremely disappointed,  the taste was an absolutely amateur boring nothing special,  will never come to this restaurant ever again , wasted my money!
Good quality, generous servings, affordable prices. What more can you ask for

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Lovely food. The pan-fried pork buns and fried thick noodles with cabbage and mushrooms are my favourites. Place is clean, comfortable and the service is very good too. It's also less crowded because it's not in a shopping mall. Recommended.

Probably best known for their $12 fish head, food was good but service level may vary depending on when you head down.

Dinner times are busy and seats might be hard to come by.
Rich taste lor mee. Overall is great. Prawn noodle is okay, I think it will taste better if add a bit of lor mee soup
My favorite dish from this Zi char  stall

Very nice pork ribs and pork burger! Pork ribs are tender and flavourful! Love the fries too! Crispy and crunchy!

Lavender honey ice cream is very nice! Lavender smell very strong and not too sweet. Charcoal Waffle is crispy too!

Good service too!
Food is average but the soyu is not suitable for sashimi.

This is a hidden gem. U will end up becoming a regular once u gon there.
Its a family run outlet. Very well managed. Good food and even better service.
No wonder they only open for dinner and remain occupied.
We usually reach by 7.30 pm because by 8 they start to have a queue.
The last orders are at 9.30.
Recommended, nice food and friendly service.

We love the food here. Highly quality and full of flavour! We especially love the salad prawns, century egg appetiser, and black pepper beef.

We did have to remind them to serve the glass of water when almost all the dishes arrived though.

Everything else was pleasant and chill.
Support local

Second visit and looking forward to a third! The service here is always excellent. I cannot vouch for their noodles but the set promo ($9.90 includes chicken, veggies, rice and a drink) is super tasty especially their house special mala chicken in a pot. Enjoy it with a hearty dollop of their homemade chilli paste/oil and the rest of your day will feel simply perfect!
Lovely ambience and tasty albeit junky food, has a nice al fresco area for pet owners and their fur kids. Deep fried chicken and croffles very yummy. Fries were good too. We'll be back soon.

To my honest opinion, the nasi lemak was just meh for me. I visited the stall because everyone was raving about it however I was somewhat disappointed that the sambal was not as nice as I was expected it to be. I mean I‚Äôve tasted better sambal elsewhere.

My cucumber was also missing from my plate. Not sure if it was intentional or not. The green lemak rice was a nice touch but it was nothing great. Price is reasonable at $3.50.

This is to my opinion.
Staff were friendly and helpful. Food was also tasty and worth the higher price. Penne Au Gratin was too bland for my liking, but the prawns inside were perfectly cooked.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Go at your own risk. No matter peak hour or non-peak hour, the staffs don‚Äôt bother taking your order although they could clearly see you standing there at the counter. Super rude and arrogant staffs. Their fish bee hoon is also no longer as nice as before, fish was not fresh and food was served cold.
Best nasi lemak in Singapore. Rice is fragrant, chicken wings are crispy. Everything on point.

Found this on sethlui intro for AMK food. Must say the clear broth chicken drum stick ramen is unexpectedly nice! Meat literally comes off using my chopstick, so no fuss! I asked for less salty and yes you can ask for it on their menu.

Humble stall selling authentic thai food in a neighbourhood coffee shop. Possibly the most popular stall in the coffee shop. Service is quick and good. Food is also great with appropriate portion sizes recommended based on the number of diners you have.
Despite its popularity, food was served up pretty quickly.
Mediocre nasi padang. Not very flavorful sambal sotong, bergerdil, and lady fingers among others. Gets the job done if you need a quick meal, but don't expect much.

Very poor management, waited for very long but the food is ready and hiding insideüôÑ
Will not patronise anymore

The service staff were very polite and helpful, restaurant vibe was good.

The food was... Interesting.
The mushroom soup is diluted and watery, there was very little mushroom taste.
Truffle fries came hot, there was some truffle oil smell but it was missing any truffle taste.
Same thing applied for the pork, ribs, sausage, chicken chop and steak. All of them were well cooked and the food texture was ok.

However, all of them didn't taste what they were suppose to taste like. The steak was slightly redeemable because of the sauce.
It's weird, this is the first time I've encountered this issue.

If you have to come and visit here, just get their beef dishes. For other Western food, there are several in the close vicinity that's better and cheaper.

Just wanted to grab a teh C after groceries shopping at NTUC on late afternoon.  Teh C more like water C. No taste of tea at all n $1.50!!! Wasn‚Äôt busy too. Hope the mgmt pick up on this and do some QC

Ordered via Grabfood and was rather disappointed overall.  It's a place for affordable, alright food but avoid the drinks.

Good
+ Affordable
+ Rather eco-friendly package
+ Appreciate thought towards packaging food and drink items properly - the noodles came in a presentable manner and even tho the drink spilled, I saw that the restaurant already used tape to tape down the cup cover to try and avoid that

Bad
- The drinks were not cheap and tasted really bad. The matcha latte cost 3.6 on Grabfood after discount but tasted like sugar water with some artifical matcha taste. Tastes like a diluted + sweetened version of those 3-in-1 matcha latte mix you can find in supermarkets, definitely not worth a few dollars
- Got the "melon milk" buddy set on Grabfood and the melon milk also tastes diluted and artificial

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Nice food everytime we get there. Standards are maintained‚ù§Ô∏èüòã
Many times came here before.. but now the prices increased! Too pricey üôà
Tasty old school Chinese food. Do try the hotplate tofu, cabbage braised chicken which pairs excellently with rice. Give the dimsum a miss.

Scrambled Egg Burger with Sausage
Fluffly scrambled egg and yummy sausage patty.

Crispy "Hainanese Chicken" Burger
Taste like McSpicy non spicy version.
Okay lah. Try once can le.
Banana Pie is Fuyoh!
Crisscut fries is standard.

Quick eats. Open sitting.
Long queue always.
Busy area.

Last few days to get spicy McNuggets.
Will miss you.

D Rubinah is a well known chain of restaurant. However, the ang mo Kio branch is quite poor interns or food variety and service.

After month of renovation, the restaurant was finally opened. After 1-2 weeks of opening, I went to try their food and was quite disappointed with the system. Even though there were 4-5 people in the kitchen, I observed that many orders were delayed and given wrongly to other customers. Thankfully, mine was not. However, I observed that the supervisor (who was also the supervisor of the previous shop there) was very demanding with the workers though they were trying hard. His constant nagging didn't help. The food is over priced weighed with the quality given. For a mutton meal, the shop worker asked whether I wanted papadam and I said okay. In a typical Indian food store (even in restaurants), papadam is not charged but here I was $1, I only got to know it when I looked at the receipt on my way back. If it is charged, they should at least tell. The rice meal was bland. Since they are new, there might be teething issue but I hope they rectify and bounce back better, soon with a good supervisor/ leader to lead.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Roti prata is fluffy and light with slight crisp on the top and bottoms. Ask for sambal to enhance the flavors

Tantanmen is nice, tastes more like Chinese cuisine instead of Japanese Ramen though
Takagi Ramen is also nice, quite thick broth, flavourful
Gyoza and Takoyaki is average, don't feel like it's worth the price
Matcha Latte is tasting close to Starbucks'

So why the missing 2 stars?
For starter, there are fly fly throughout our meal
Then, I saw a drop of üíß attacking my Gyoza!! When I look up, yes indeed the Airconditioner is there...
So yea, the 2 missing stars are due to the environment, very bad, I'd be trying other outlets for the ramen, but not this outlet, scared liao üòÜ

I mean..., such a waste to lose points in environment..., maybe some renovations should take place ü§î

Writing this makes me really upset because i was here yesterday to celebrate my mom's birthday. This place is an absolute disappointment and has horrendous customer service. First off, called for a reservation for 20 pax at 830pm because people are coming from work and hence the late timing. However, the staff on the phone kept insisting and being so pushy with me by telling me that I should come earlier because the last order was at 930pm. Not only that, they do not respect my boundaries as they wanted to confirm my table by spam calling me 5 times while i am at work.

Then, managed to get everyone to come earlier and the waitress was so pushy towards the items we want to order by saying we should get abalone dishes. However, not everyone likes to eat such dishes because we have people that are not local and Chinese which doesn't suit their taste. But the staff was super insistent about it which cmon, once again be professional. You guys are a Michelin star restaurant.

The worse of all, dishes came out so fast that every time each waitress comes, 4 dishes comes out at the same time. You got to pace the food timings because if you rushed all the dishes out, the other dishes are going to be cold and it affects the texture, taste and quality of the food. Then, staff still argued that they have no control over this. Cmon, you obviously can just tell the chefs at the back to slow down with the food. I know you want to faster get your job done and close the shop early but we are here celebrating and we arent that unreasonable to stay till late night. Also, We are ordering approximately close to 10 dishes for each table and food got to be served at a moderate pace. Worse of all, staff even went to argue and retaliate against our request. Is this even reasonable?

To end off, my family have been spending at least hundreds of dollars every visit  when we come to putien because we find that food is decent, a nice location to be and also a place my family can bond together. Yet, none of the staff remembered us and this place does not value their regular customers. Very disappointing really...
Inexpensive nice food. Beside lamian, they have many other food like fried fish, ma la tofu..etc. only con is place too small.

The Masala Tea is is acceptable, the plain prata is soft & warm. The restaurant is laidback relaxing. The price is affordable. It would be great if they can expend the restaurant since they isnt much seats and the restaurant have potential. Reccomended.

Great all-day brunch and coffee. I had the open faced wagyu sandwich and my wife tried the Rosti waffle platter which is gluten free. Both are well presented and tasty. It is cavernous inside with lots of space and good ambience. Pets are allowed in their outdoor seating, which is nice!
Had the $9.80 pork katsu don. Flavour and portion were both better than average, but not particularly outstanding.

Used to work in Jurong and this was the go to place beside Jurong Hill Park, for a Japanese lunch.

Surprised to see that the restaurant is still doing well after 20 years, even though all the other establishments around the same area have gone to the pits. Sure it needs a new coat of paint but something tells me it‚Äôs not going to happen.

We ordered sashimi, tonkatsu don and grilled chicken set. Food still tastes good although prices have gone up a lot. The sashimi was fresh and thick cut, not the thin slivers of fish you get else where. The grilled chicken (salted, not teriyaki) was a little under cooked in some parts but mostly okay. The tonkatsu was crunchy with every bite and juicily tender inside.

I strongly recommend this old school Japanese restaurant for a simple no frills Japanese meal. Great value for money.
Had a nice gathering with friends in the past week. The food is good value for price. The fish and chips was done nicely.
The customer service here is great and the waiting time is not considered long for me. The food is also very appetising and delicious.

After receiving my drink, most of the ice already 3/4 melted. So I went to ask for more ice added. The boss himself added the ice for me. Upon payment I was told my drink (Ice lemon tea) cost $4. I was shocked & asked why so expensive? The staff said my drink was $2.50 & the added ice was $1.50! I ask why so expensive for ice & he said extra ice is $1. So now from $1.50 become $1. I said it's too expensive to the staff & it was reduce again this time to 50cents. I'm never coming back to this place again & I'd advise anyone the same as well.

Awesome food, awesome service! I must say they are very polite and friendly. Seen how some customers talk very rudely to them and they endure it all. Hats off to the team. Will continue to support them and recommend them to my family and friends!

‚ÄúRestaurant standard Hawker price‚Äù is what you will find on their signboard instead of Konomi Zen which is not reflected.

Past them by so many times but never bothered to try so today finally ordered their Teriyaki chicken set.
It‚Äôs lunch time there‚Äôs not much of a Q, but the customer flow is quite consistent.

The boss/Chef has an aura about him, feels like he was the head chef of some high end Japanese Omakase restaurant.
Back to their teriyaki chicken set. At $4.50 it is quite a steal if u compare it with Sakae Shushi.

I believe they use calrose rice (short grain type), it was a bit dry.
The chicken itself was oki, but becomes an impact when u eat it with their panko
Came with a fried sweet potato which was fantastic.

Overall it‚Äôs an oki but affordable Japanese lunch.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Modified Hunan food‚Ä¶ but tasty
Ingredients are fresh and value for money. Tastes good too!

Worst sushi I ever had in my life.. The sushi‚Äôs rice is over-cooked and it became like a porridge-liked sticky texture. An obviously untrained waitress (who has no idea what customer service means, even after i filed a complaint and being nice not to be fussy, she has not say a word from her mouth, not even a ‚Äòsorry‚Äô or ‚Äòthank you‚Äô). Lastly, an ah Beng chef who speak loudly behind the kitchen saying, it is not my fault by the rice fault....... what an experience and I will not recommend anyone to patronise this shop.
An authentic Singapore presentation of traditional Chinese Noodles & Dumplings that has endured for 3 decades ‚Ä¶
Expensive, small serving.

Wagyu beef is blend and tough. Rather pay extra to buy from Waacow. Or downgrade to buy beef bowl from tasty street Pasir Ris. Looks good but don't taste nice. Would give 1 star but added 1 more as it is Halal (hard to find halal donburi)
Staff are extremely slow and have no sense of urgency. Even the delivery riders have to queue up when all their orders are not settled. They do not seem to be bothered that they are slow.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Nice food and  reasonable prices, what's there not to patronize?

They are also very proactive to take your orders, unlike some places where they seem to intentionally ignore you because they are onto something else.

Newly opened foodcourt with plenty of seats. Teh C is such a big cup costing only $1.80. Penang fried kway teow is well fried but popiah is a big let down. This place is fully packed after 11.30am so if you want to enjoy your food please come early.

Malaysia street foods and it's delicious. I'll say quite close to the taste I ate in Malaysia. Maybe the dining environment is different so you don't really feel the same. Price is similar to other food courts. At least it is a change from the usual food choices we have in other food courts.

Really rude malaysian staff. Ordered foodpanda self pickup, they badmouth me when i was right there. Say in chinese ‚Äúask that person that order come and i‚Äôll f him‚Äù lol ORDERED POPCORN CHICKEN $5. 5 FREAKING DOLLARS. COME LESS THAN 10 piece lmao. When i told him im right here, they just keep quiet and stop talking about it. Not happy go back la ccb
Food was great and excellence

I believe in the category of coffeeshop western food this is the best I have eaten so far. I ordered chicken chop and it‚Äôs nicely grilled whereby it is not over cooked and dry and not rare and undercooked. Taste profile might be considered less flavourful by many but alright by me. Feel like this way I can taste the actual taste of the raw material and not just flavouring and msg. Side dish is curly fries which is fried skilfully such that it is not served drenched in oil. I just noticed I used a lot of ‚Äúnot‚Äù expression to describe the food here. It‚Äôs is definitely not what you get at all coffeeshop western food stores out there.
Good service, well-priced menu and the best halo-halo ( Filipino dessert, like ice kacang but way better because it has more fresh ingredients ), in Singapore!  Cozy place :)
Ordered chicken cutlet and pork chop fried rice. Too salty for our taste. Generous portions of meat but overall the taste becomes too much. I hope to try again with more subtle flavours

Delicious Japanese food. Genki sushi idea. Food quality is slightly cheaper than genki and almost as good as genki, but I‚Äôll still feel that genki taste better. Food preparing can be slightly longer. 5 stars if the timing for food to come is faster. Quality is good enough for this price.

I ordered Flamed Grilled Chicken with 2 sides - baked potato and hot veggies. The highlight is the flamed grilled chicken with the tic tac toe marks - they make you wanna play with it. But my stomach said, "Feed me!" So I did. And lovin' it (even without the chicken gravy). By the way, don't get fooled by the thin looking chicken meat. It has no skin or fatty parts so you are getting real flame grilled meat. I wish I have 1 more stomach within me for another piece of chicken!

Superb service. I was initially confused when they didnt let me and my lil one sit at a vacant 2 seater, but realised they take seriously 1st come, first served and were planning to rearrange those seats for the group of 3 before us. They were also v kind to let me and my tired kid wait for seats inside at the sofa area and made my kid's day with a free lollipop. They cashier was very good in that she asked me first if it was ok, before offering the candy to my son. Very impressed by the service and kindness :) Thank you!

I think semma singapore, has a mix of culture, ambience and great food. All the food was extremely amazing and tasty but my fav has to be the sizzling mysore mutton! I have ate mysore mutton in many places, but the sizzling mysore mutton, at semma singapore, has the perfect blend of spices to it, the cashew with dried chilli with the mutton being so tender, was definitely something i enjoyed. I liked the blend of drinks, and the service as well. I love the fact that the owners were so hospitable to their customers and made them feel like home. I would totally recommend Semme Singapore to anybody, who loves  to have a blend of great ambience, service, food, drinks and music! Everyone of you should so try it!

Very rude staff service. The staff accidentally opened the door and knocked on my mum. Instead of making appologize, the staff told my mum should not use that path. If this was not a walkway, shouldn't you put a signboard there. Shouldn't you appologize as a basic manner?  I spoke the manager but the manager just pretended busy and did not take any remedial action for the rude behavoiur of his staff. Bad service n will not cime back again.

A very homy style of restaurant. Condiments are self serving, free seating. Staff are nice and easy.
Tried their bee hoon goreng... sedap!! Delicious! Be it with mutton, chicken or other or just plain, is simple and good.
Roti John also a good try too, you can request for more ketchup or mayonnaise... mmmm...
Lastly,  their drinks are good and has a variety to choose from!!
Spoilt!!
Only thing is, their nasi(rice) still have room for improvement.
Overall, good place for small gather or dine alone.

I LOVE THIS. Wholesome comfort food. And I'm so disappointed they don't deliver further or offer their own delivery because the NTU campus is so far in. I'm obsessed with the cheese pasta, seaweed tofu and scrambled eggs üòç
Fantastic nasi lemak at a great price. Beef rendang is tender and not too salty, blue pea coconut rice is delish. Thanks for the great delivery order

Will happily go back to eat the set A with the fried chicken wing. Added on: Eggplant & curry veg ‚úÖnice crispy anchovies and peanuts. Most of the food was cold by the time I was there about 8pm, but was still good. They were still frying certain food items but mostly sold out.

It is located at Blk 555 Ang Mo Kio Ave 10.It is a neighbourhood Chinese restaurant serving Northern Chinese and Szechuan cusuines.The restaurant is not big in size , so sitting capacity is limited.The restaurant is quite vacant in the day and gets alittle busier in the evenings during dinner time.On Sundays the business is better.The food standards depends on individuals as taste and preferences for foods differs individually
Example if you like Northern Chinese or Szechuan ( Hot & Spicy ) foods , then you may like the foods.Parking wise is easy at the HDB car park behind.Public busstop is also just at the road ( Ang Mo Kio Ave 10 ) infront, quite convenient also.

Dated : 09/04/ 2019 ( Tuesday ).
Posted 2 photos.
There is no updated timing for operating hour, the staff rejected us for dining between 3:30-4:30 when the shop is operating

1st time having this as heard many said nice. No problem eating alone as the way they design it.  Waiting time is ok, all digitalize made everything fast and simple.  Self collect the raw meat at the collection counter.  Everyone give  50 mins only.
Nice meat but perhaps need more for me ü§£ü§£

Great pricing and for the quality and freshness well deserves the 5 stars. Located in a well hidden industrial building you will need to be intentional in seeking this place out but rest assured you'll be rewarded with some of the tastiest mentai salmon and pork jowl dishes. They have fresh sashimi too! Well worth a visit or two or three! When u are in the area.

It's a chicken rice place, so we ordered chicken rice. The steamed chicken was great and the sauce was really good. The prawn roll and crispy tofu were tasty too. Service was very good, prompt and friendly. This place is walk-in only and didn't take reservations.

My grandchildren got excited with the DIY popiah and the peking duck, hands on meal.

The restaurant also did a salt and pepper fry with the duck carcass so nothing was wasted. However, the peking duck crepes were dry, especially the top layer, perhaps due to poor packing for delivery. The popiah skin was ok and did not dry out like the crepes for the duck.

The dumplings were meaty and juicy. I also like the four season beans with minced meat. The fried noodle texture was a tad tough for my liking although the taste (seasoning) was spot on.

Overall, it was a very memorable delivered meal which we enjoyed.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Staff treats customers badly. Did not show price and got mad at me indirectly when I asked and changed my order when it was too expensive. The cashier also did not get my order right because when i told them I was dining in, they packeted my food to take away. Food was a 6/10. Also it was too expensive.
Food poisoning and diarrhoea for me and my entire family including the elderly, after dabao-ing. Not even fantastic. Eat at yr own risk

This definitely hidden gem at Westgate. that serves awesome Charcoal-grilled Japanese skewers. It may not be the most prominent eatery on the level, but its modest shopfront belies the delicious food that it has to offer.
Reasonable & affordable price...

A good Indian restaurant in neighbour around Yishun church. They sell South Indian Halal food. The restaurant is stretched over 4 shops in a raw selling a large verity of Indian food. Their Prata Bom (prata with cheese and condensed milk in it) tastes great. Will go again for sure.
Fish and chips $6. Big portion.

My go-to place if I would like to have something nice but still affordable.

The staffs in this branch are really friendly. The aunties and uncles were working here for many years. I hope this place can survive this covid situation.

I usually ordered steak here, and personally I found their steak is one of the best in Singapore. The meat retain the juiciness of the meat. It is also tender.

Expected damage would be around 25-35 per pax (depending what you ordered). They offer lunch set menu which is super affordable and worth the value. You can check on their website.

The place is always packed.
However, the Service is good n fast.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: The jajangmyeon (black bean sauce noodles) and fried dumplings (tasted like curry puff) were not bad. From an earlier visit, enjoyed the Ïû°Ï±Ñ japchae (stir fried glass noodles and vegetables) and the ÍπÄÏπòÏ†Ñ kimchijeon (kimchi pancake).

Delicious family-run restaurant which has been around for generations. Hopefully it will continue to be around for longer in to the future.

Their salted chicken, braised pork with vegetables and tofu are all amazing. My favourites dishes. Great every time!
Food is good with many choices, the drinks are very pricey though (a normal cup of iced milk tea for $2.70...)

This rating is rounded up from 3.5. The food is fresh and fast and the sauces to add to the dishes are delicious, but there was hardly any chicken in my burrito, it was mostly (plain) rice. Disappointing for Mexican, but OK if you have a craving in Singapore.

Fast service and taste of food served is consistently good. Special mention for Thai honey chicken wings, kuayteow goreng, salted egg dishes and the chyesim soup with salted egg.
Friendly staff, esp Sally and Xi Ren
Nice Breakfast Indian Hala Food

Mid quality Japanese rice that‚Äôs not really chewy, and clumps together. Skewers are a rendition of Tori-Q, but &Joy does it slightly better. Tempura is made of breaded flour and not actual tempura batter. Soggy and inner filling is so so. Tamago egg is a little too salty. Fried rice is just soya sauce with rice. Almost tasteless.

Ambience and service is good though however.

Very lazy staff, apparently my takeaway order was on the table for a good 10 minutes while the staff was talking to each other before they went to check it and gave the food to me.

This is not the first incident I've experienced with this outlet, both from me and my friends. There has been times that they forgot our order to the point where I had to wait for 30 mins before they were done with the order, granted it was busy when that particular incident happened.

The only time you can get good service from them is when there's no one at the outlet. Maybe they will only make the effort when there's no business there.

If you really want to eat at Srisun, just make the effort to go to the Serangoon Garden outlet. I have experience good service there so I don't understand why the standards are not the same for all their outlets.
Nice teochew resturant, 24hrs dim sum available. Fish steamboat smells really good, Will definitely come back to try again.

Came here few times ,use like the fish soup here and dim sum. Fish head steamboat. Decided to write feedback here ..think is my last time here ..  the service really BAD .. no one asking you or bother you want to dine in ? We stand big there quite sometime and keep asking for a table .. the restaurant seem not full occupied.. And then waited to place order .. they serve wrong food , and they even say sorry and the staff look like very busy to answer you .. the fish soup not as nice as last few times we came .Service too bad , price also increased a lot  won‚Äôt think coming back again. !

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: They are short handed and staff stretched to the max but they still open up the entire place. End result is they have to rush like mad compromising customer service and food. I been to this outlet many times,  all I can say is they are on a slippery road down in terms of service.
Probably the best prawn paste chicken and fish beehoon soup in sg. All time favourite.

For the pricing of this restaurant, the food is definitely not up to the mark.  There are many more better Teochew restaurants in town, that charge the same price, but serve much better quality food.  Do not bother to try.
Nice and cosy place to chill out. Food was great, reasonably priced and better than expected. Gary and team provided excellent service.
I ordered a Kadai  chicken delivery , but I received something like chicken manchurian with bad taste .. useless restaurant to place your take away ..

Basically good ol‚Äô chicken rice with upscale zichar vibes!

Some dishes such as their classic steamed chicken and ÁÇíÁ≤íÁ≤íwere delicious, whereas some really bordered on being too salty (the braised tofu with seafood had wayyyyy too much sodium than needed)

Prices are also much higher than your regular kopitiam chicken rice, but that‚Äôs reasonable for the location and the fact that it‚Äôs a standalone restaurant.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
System is not very friendly, but staff is nice to guide us. It's very nice to see a group of cheerful group helping us not so up to technology batch..

Seems abit under Staffs as they are moving up and down very quickly...

Overall, experience is great.. Jus not very good with thr phone ordering.
Tasty food, but they sell normal prata for $1.50 a bit expensive but there is nothing special about it.
Food was nice and good. Nice serving portion. Good spread. They have sets. Staff was friendly.
Cheap and good

Moderate size Din Tai Fung. Service was excellent as always and queue moved rather quickly compared to other outlets. Food was good too, however their baos were totally not worth it. Their red bean bao especially, the red bean paste wasn't smooth and tasted terrible.

a phenomenal dining experience! my second time back at tanoke and the experience was as good as the first. The highlight of the night had to be the Otoro Aburi Handroll- definitely order this. The other dishes we ordered were spectacular as well but as the night progresses I got really full as the portions are pretty substantial! This is not a bad thing surely if you come in a big group and reservations are incredibly easy to make for some reason! The dishes took very long to be served hence the deduction of 1 star. If you are not ravenous this place would be perfect for a quiet date night
Rare gem found in Singapore, foods serve here was nice, you can imagine the satisfication of 3 pax from the pictures post here~ üòù(don't doubt on us, it's really 3 pax only in total)

Pretty unique foods not frequently seen in SG. The pan fried bun signature of theirs is very good. However the other dishes are quite average tasting.

Service was very good, and food came quite quickly.
Really awesome prata with mutton dalsa. Highly recommend this shop. Service also very Nice. Special is mutton dalsa!!

update as of Apr 22: Price increase. Sour veg fish is now $20+. not sure if its me, but i felt the fish slices has also reduced. Skewers price also went up.

Had a craving for sour veg fish and saw review for this place is not bad. It did not disappoint! $18 for the dish and portion is generous and the soup super appetising! Tries the skewers and love the spices they sprinkled on it. Decent prices, good taste and did not gave too wait too long. Will be back!

Mediocre food and long wait for food even though the restaurant was not crowded.
The ramen was soggy and starchy. The stock was underwhelming and was almost room temperature.
The chirashi don was worse. The sashimi pieces were very thinly sliced so much so that can't taste the fish. The rice at least was like normal rice.
The gyoza was very oily. There was meant to be 6 pieces of gyoza but we were served 5. Had to ask for missing piece.
Unlikely to go back ever.

My husband ordered Tom Yum Fried Rice from here for us and asked the lady multiple times to not add any seafood/fish aside from prawns into the rice. When he got home we found seafood in the dish, what a waste of food and money as we cannot eat.
Cheap and nice nasi lemak. Lontong is nice too. Q was long but move fast.
Have a Yummy nasi lemak at Sedap!

Went on Thur 2pm for mee rebus.
Ordered power ($4.8) and extra ($6.3). Extra come with drumstick which I find it bland and not really tender.
But the gravy when mixed with satay sauce goes well the noodles.

Ordered ribeye (medium rare) for $16 & chicken cutlet for $7.

Sauce for the ribeye was pretty tasty and meat done-ness was done just right. As for the chicken cutlet, quite average. Coleslaw was nice!

My first time dining in here and it was superb! It‚Äôs has the local Chinese restaurant vibe, place was immaculate and their staff were friendly and efficient. The menu had many varieties, like the geoduck sashimi which I thought was pretty cool! The food was fragrant and tasty, I really enjoyed the garlic pork and the duck! their de-shelled cereal prawn and dark sauce hokkien mee was good too. For dessert, we had mango pudding and I must say it exceeded my expectations. I‚Äôll definitely come back here again and recommend to friends.
Best for price Chicken Katsudon. Quality is consistent here. Been here many times over last 8 years. Tastes awesome. You wont be disappointed

Can see that the staff put a lot of effort into preparing the food (was observing one of them putting on the garnishing). The food tastes even better than the outlet in Canberra Plaza. Thumbs up!

Not to mention you can use CDC voucher here so it‚Äôs definitely worth it!

One of the best nasi lemak ever. I am not even exaggerating. I had the rendang set with achar instead of sayur lodeh. Beef Rendang was tender and flavourful. Fried egg has runny yolk just the way I like it. A generous portion of nuts and anchovies. The most important piece of this plate of deliciousness, the sambal. There are 4 sambal to choose from, unable to decided the lady gave me two to try out and even offer a top up later. In my opinion, the portion was perfect, i had a delicious lunch. There are a lot of customisation options available so you can build your own perfect plate of nasi lemak. Highly recommend this place. Definitely coming back.
Yummy and tasty hakka food. Quick service, down to earth place. Very home-ly place and we love it!

Love my dinner there. The interior was really cute and attractive. Was lots of fun even for adults to have their food come in the cute bots. Every time it opens, we get a surprise, more hygienic than the other similar concept. The staff were very polite as well. Understand there might be some teething issues due to the sudden hype which is pretty normal. Hope everyone get to try Sushigo at least once!

We happened to step in to this place by luck due to our prior bad experience with another Bistro. We were super surprised with the food choices, quality and taste of the food. The gold plating was the service offered by Wei Meng, we loved it.. Thanks for making our Sunday evening blissful.. Highly Recommend this Heroic place..
Like a secret clubhouse. We enjoyed the drinks and food. It's not the cheapest sake place to chill but worth the trip. Kanpai üç∂ü•≥

The fried fish head soup steamboat is excellent. The sliced fish is very fish and smooth. Good broth that the staff keep topping up. The egg was a bit salty, the spring was ok, not bad. The pu er tea taste a bit different. Will be back to try the 24hra dim sum dishes too
Small eating place but cam accommodate about 50 pax at one time. Good quality prata and very crispy. Curry is available for unlimiyed top up. Must try when you are nearby.

Me and husband like this place a lot
Generous portion of tasty pork bone soup- prob twice the size of a normal bowl of ramen - more then enough soup for 2 adults
Can customise carbo with toppings
Reasonable pricing
Every bowl is freshly prepared and consistency is there each time!
Will recommend esp if u have a friend or partner! Otherwise 1 bowl might appear daunting haha

Excellent service form the crew, especially the restaurant lady manager.

Highly customer focus, provides good recommendation and very attentive to customer needs.

Great Cantonese food with good promotions, on top of that you get a 155 discount!

The Ireland peking duck is stunning, juicy, plump and delicious. It is succulent, very tender and nicely de-skinned by the staff right in front of you, perfectly wrapped in the serving skin with a nice sauce.

Shark's fin was excellent with this promotional price, served piping hot, HUGE piece of whole fin. The broth is so tasty, topped with bean sprouts

Wasabi prawns is good, could be better if the wasabi flavour be more pronounced, that's purely personal as some people may not be able to take the heat

Char siew and roast pork are to die for! good layers of fat for the char siew and roast pork flavour is good with a crispy skin

Overall dishes looks good. Been there twice already and making plans for the 3rd visit.

To the crew and chef, keep it UP. It's a good restaurant that bothers to keep their image and service, under any circumstances.

B2 of Westgate outside Hao Mart.

Have to order ahead before seating.

Tables are cleaned with cleanser after each patron as I've seen it done.

4 stars cause they're Japanese grill but the options are limited and has kimchi on their don. Kimchi is a nice touch though.

Meat are grilled nice, not too oily which pairs well with the rice. If you're going to have this as first meal or is a big eater, you should order more.

Had pork belly and chicken thigh which were nice. Someone mentioned looks homemade in their review and I tend to agree but isn't homemade nicer and more flexible in the ingredients?

I would be there again to try others.

A rare find to find a great steak house in the heartlands. The staff here are so friendly, and service is rather prompt too. If you're stuck for choice, they wouldn't mind recommending what to eat. Another thing I like is that they're pet friendly, so pet owners feel free to bring your pups or cats along, as long as they're leashed.
Food here is pretty delicious too. I enjoy a good steak and the sides here are delectable. They have one of the better Mac and Cheese sides I've eaten compared to some other steakhouses. Definitely a bang for your buck considering the range they have here.

Only Nasi Lemak is offered. The sambal is special and good tasting.
No fish if you are late after 10am.
Fried chicken wings rather small.
No cucumber.
Not worth the long queue
Neighborhood restaurant that offers Ala Carte and several good value set options. There are sets for elderly $6.90 and students $7.90. High tea sets at $5.90.

I would like to complain about how bad of a service the cashier is, rudely asking for orders and it was my first time ordering and not only that the person uses the same gloves to take food and cash and I find it very unsanitary. I hope this can change, I really love the food.
Good service, helpful staff. I must say that they have since upgraded their rojak sauce, it is now comparable to Ministry of Rojak.
Nice food
Fast and value for money.

Tried their green curry, grilled pork stick and basil pork. The food is authentically thai and priced reasonably.

Will definitely come again to try other food in the menu.
Worth the money to go for a buffet! Owner was very nice and attentive to constantly check on us and topped up our soup without asking. She even gave us satay! Chill and pleasant to eat üòÄ

2nd visit - Self service for this stall. The rojak taste nice and fresh but the pricing a bit on the high end. Teh tarik was good. As there are limited seating area thus it quite hard to find a table during peak hour but you are allowed to seat at the foodcourt seating area.
Great food with good ambience. Will definitely visit again. A portion of nasi briyani is good for 2 people.

Pretty tasty steak, had a ribeye for 20 sgd, price is net, there was no gst and service charge. Overall was well cooked and tasty steak, came with fries that were crispy, and some salad. Overall ambience is decent and comfy, was not crowded on a Saturday afternoon. They have pasta and grilled chicken at more affordable prices around 10 dollars.
Few years back it is nice and affordable but now ‚Ä¶. the most expensive nasi padang for coffeeshop.
So lousy service as well the food. Better go food court.. much more cheaper and nice.for take away charge extra with poor packaging.. paper box. (Sambal and rice spill all over the box)
Service was great! Very friendly staff, food was really tasty and the lunch deals are really worth it! Particularly enjoyed the Omelette and Mango Sticky Rice! Definitely a must try!
Green iced tea is super sweet, basil chicken not good, garlic pork just ok. I won‚Äôt come back. For the price there are much better tasting options.
Affordable sushi price. I have tried their salmon mentai don, not so suit my taste but there was good taste for normal sushi. Normally have long queue during lunch and dinner time.
Phone ordered red bean crispy pancake for takeaway. Collection and payment was a breeze. Repeat purchase, Yummy!
Delicious halal peranakan food in AMK. Food Delivery service by Honestbee. Their food is delicious and tasty.Lots of variety dishes to choose. Must try food in AMK.

Presentation full marks! The prettiest bowl of chirashi I have ever eaten! Portions are very generous too, so if you are a small eater, the mini bowl is plenty. Flavour isn‚Äôt the traditional kind so come with an open mind. Overall a great meal in a fuss-free residential joint, cosy and friendly staff. Definitely worth a try!
Your food is always tasty, fresh cooked and your prices are very reasonable. Please go on doing quality. We all need it.

Service is ok but probably because there isn't crowd at all.

Price for a such small establishment is very very steep. Easily matching almost to Sushi Tei.

Food taste is very average at best. Taste frozen. The flour used for the tempura is food court standard. Serving is also very small.

Considering the taste versus the price, wouldn't visit again. I spent $30 alone for the food which i can get at $15 at Sushi Express and taste better.
Pretty busy place on a weekend night. Good variety of local favourite foods like zi char, Indian Muslim, Western grill and Korean Army Stew, supported by a well-stocked beer fridge.
Quiet and Cosy Cafe. Signature woody decor. Great place to meet friends.  Service is quick.  Prices are reasonable.

Haven't been there in years, and I'm glad they are still around. I was pleasantly surprised to see that they offer DIY popiah, as I don't remember them having it on their menu. We ordered a set to try. The portions were good for 2-3 persons, with 6 popiah skins. I wish they had provided more skins as they tend to break. The ingredients were great, very delicious and fresh. The garlic paste and chilli sauce both pack a punch, so you might want to go easy on them at first. I didn't see any dried shrimp nor fresh prawns, so I think this dish is suitable for vegetarians as well.
The ambiance was very nice, plus the courteous and friendly staff all made dining there a delightful experience. Well worth checking out if you're around the area.
üëç üòã Chicken tasty üêî rice and fried bean curd with hard crust but soft üî• inside.
Wonderful place to hang out with friends
Rude incorrigible boss or staff.
The chefs are helpful here. We came for a corporate event. The ingredients are measured out already.
Ramen is average. Sashimi is way below average. There are better Japanese restaurants. Good for quick lunch though.
Reasonable price with good portion size üëçüëç we're here for their Fish Curry and briyani
Rice is cold and a bit hard to chew. Beef is cold also
Should reduce the gravy colouring ,must be hot üî• and spicy. Try to imitate the gravy of 1960's at Bras Basah Rd.

Food is decent , the chef presentation is good n have their own style which is different. Price is good , portion is generous but I think they can work on their coffee when it comes to breakfast..other than that it's worth the time and money . Good job guys
Nice food options, great taste, friendly staff, bang for the buck, descent vibe, a tick on all the boxes. Must try place

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: All staff with excellent service especially a guy named Shariff! I requested Thai milk tea with less ice and everytime I want to refill water, he will make sure the ice not fall into my drink.
It's not bad. The food is good, service good. The tables are rather small though. 7 people eaten at a table of 4 is rather squeeze....

Yummy and crispy Spring chicken. The chicken chop on hotplate is nice too.
Worth to try!

Newly opened branch at Compassone about 2 weeks ago. Conveniently located a short walk from Sengkang MRT after walking straight down with Polar Puffs and Cakes on right, BTK is on the left. Restaurant has crowd waiting for takeaway and to dine in. Am glad it didn‚Äôt take too long for me to queue for takeaway. It only took 15mins for me and the customer before me to receive our takeaways. Maybe because it‚Äôs a little chaotic in the kitchen, some customers with queue numbers earlier than me were skipped.

The takeaways were very nicely packed with all sauces and sturdy cutlery set given. The Chicken rice tastes similar to BTK at Boon Keng. Takeaways are also available on Deliveroo.

We had the sirloin and chicken chop fried rice. Both were yummy!  Medium rare was more medium than rare but the flavour was great.  The giant potato hall was a nice change from the usual fries/baked potato.  Chicken chop was grilled really well, almost crispy skin.  Be ready to wait during peak lunch hour
Not bad, the taste of the food is much better then when the newly opened

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content:
Tian Yuan Xiang SG - Áî∞ÂéüÈ¶ô Êñ∞Âä†Âù°'s drip chicken essence has a sweet light taste to it. Even though it is a concentrated double-boiled chicken broth with no water added to it, it has a clean fresh savoury flavour. Since the best time to consume it is between morning to 4pm, i will usually feed it to the kids before sending them to school.

Tian Yuan Xiang original drip chicken essence  is individually packed in frozen sachets. It only use natural chicken (free from drugs or injections) and the meat are Halal Certified. To consume it, you can either heat it up in a bowl of hot water or simple put in a microwave for few minutes. So convienent.
Malay cuisines with taste food

The food was excellent and the service was quick. We went right before dinner time and managed to skip the queue but on weekends and during holidays, the restaurant can fill up fast and you may need to queue for a while.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: One of the best korean Chinese restaurants in SG.

First time trying their zi char and I would say that service and food are both relatively above average.

There are a few order takers so you will never be neglected, unless there‚Äôs a huge crowd who wants their order taken at the same time.

Upon ordering, the food came out in less than 10 minutes. This amazed me as I expected to wait for about 10-15 minutes.

Food is well seasoned and relatively fresh, given that they are always very crowded every night and opens till quite late at night for the supper crowd. The food is tasty even though it is halal.

A lot of seatings and turnaround is fast, so don‚Äôt have to worry there‚Äôs no seats.

Plus, the tables are clean compared to a lot of coffee shops.

Will definitely come back again to try their seafood fried rice as I saw a few who came to packet seafood fried rice.
Volcano prata, something special at Tasha's, quality food with in-house dough. Extremely impressed. Will be back often.
Dusty and dirty.. even the food is nice and service is good, but the hygiene at the counter table is just awful, how come no one take care of these basic hygiene ?
Questionable food quality in this particular branch towards the end of day. Comes free with explosive diarrhea on occasion. You're in it to win it
Take away the Katsu don . Will try their curry next time

It was our first time to visit this restaurant

I like the ambience and location of the restaurant.

Portion and taste of the food is good
Price was comparable to others
Customer service was almost great, just observed that not everyone is happy to serve.
Food was good especially the peking duck.  Beef was tender and tasty. Dim sum was just normal and expensive at about 5.xx per basket.  If there is no promotion,  don't think is worth for the price.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Hwang Sil is a great place for Korean-style Chinese comfort food. Their noodle dishes are nice and the mains come in a range of sizes. They also have quite a few combos and set menus that include the most popular dishes. I recommend trying the kkanpunggi (ÍπêÌíçÍ∏∞). The sweet and sour pork (ÌÉïÏàòÏú°) is also good.

BEST PLACE IN SG FOR SATTI SORRU.
Food tastes like home cooked food.
Price is worth the taste.
The prawn Masala and Naan Combo Is out of the world

There was a queue but there were many empty tables too. I asked if we need to make reservation. Service staff turned me down with a bad attitude and asked me to get back to queue. I was merely asking and wondered why many people have queued when there are so many empty tables. I have not tried the food but certainly have zero tolerance for poor service. Well so what you have good food but that is not an excuse for poor service. Not sure if food is good. Instead I went to Bangkok J N Thai food along Balestier Road. Great food, great service at awesome price.

If there is a zero star, it will be given.

Really wanted Mala Xiang Guo and thought this shop would be it. But turns out it wasn‚Äôt even spicy or flavourful.

The sauce was diluted with water and not enough herbs or spice to stir fry the ingredients. Was Disappointed as it is run by china natives.

Won‚Äôt think I‚Äôll be back here again. üòûüòï

This store at United Square is warm and friendly. The captain that served us has been very accommodating, letting us have seats of our choice, and served us politely, professionally.
The store manager also did her best to arrange the dishes in a way that suits our style. Lastly, one of male staff attended to our needs every now and then.
Really customized service!
The ambience of the restaurant is great too, where a section actually faces a garden.
Overall, great experience!!
This place got nice food with big portion. However, the counter staff (aunty) is quite rude and not friendly

1st time ordering from this restaurant, most staffs are quite ok but I‚Äôm impressed by a young pretty girl named Tong..
She was extremely polite and helpful, never gave me the feeling of any impatient or frustration vibes when I actually asked her alot of question regard the costs, packaging of the food for take away etc.. I must admit that I took up quite a while of her times. Thank you Tong for your good services & recommendation of all dishes, my whole family really enjoyed all the dishes.
Good food at reasonable pricing..
will come back to dine in next time..

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Jjamppong(Ïß¨ÎΩï) and raw beef(Ïú°Ìöå) are the best in Singapore.
Other menus are also above average.

Quite disappointing.. the food which i ordered here taste sadly poor compared to their sister restaurant at Capitol Piazza‚Äôs Famous Treasure. KL noodles is too sweet and no wok hei fragrant. Flower crab is having promotion, buy 1 get 1, is a joke. when serve on our table i really got shock of my life. Why? Is just so small small small. The crab size is like abt 1/3 size of wat i had at capitol.  Really sad is so small and the chef overcook it and the meat become dry and shrink. And taste really no match to capitol. content: Always return here when I happen to pass by the area. They sell affordable sushi with decently good quality (sushi express quality) and fresh. Bought the salmon don for $6 and it was really filling. Another fav is the salmon duo which is 10pcs of salmon sushi for $5. What a steal!

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Been to Anjana a few times over the past couple of years but taking the opportunity to write a review after my most recent visit.

As mentioned in other reviews, I have to admit that the food quality has taken a slight dip from the time they were in the smaller space, to the time they've expanded. Seating, space and ambience is decent with outdoor seating being a plus. Service is quite alright, definitely nothing to complain about.

This time we had chicken dum biriyani and I had to admit that it was a disappointment. The naan set with mutton roganjosh was much better. One suggestion would be to possibly cut down 1 side dish in the set. But pretty much all the items in the set were tasty, and that goes for the naan too. Chicken murtabak was quite huge, a bit oily, but overall quite nice. Mango lassi a tad too thick that it was an effort to drink it using the straw :)

An 'alright' experience at Anjana, though the food is no doubt good, I believe it lacks consistency - unlike the last time. So an improvement in that department would do wonders.
not halal

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Reasonable pricing. Food is rather delish. Really too few staff around.

Most branches we went are quite crowded esp on Friday & weekends. Nice choices of food, kids loves their dumplings, fried rice, chicken soup & loves to watch the chef makes the dumlings! Very long queues but their services are still fast enough!

Food: Shiitake was big, juicy, chewy, not too salty, and most important it had this smoked taste that makes you feel like you're at a barbecue without suffering the heat and smoke in your hair.
Chicken thigh was smooth, juicy, slightly crunchy skin, and no charring.
Quail eggs with pork belly wasn't anything amazing though the combination was new to me and much appreciated. It might have had more impact if the pork belly was more flavorful.

Ambience: BEAUTIFUL. Excluding the one guest who spoke way too loud at times, the place was generally pretty chill. A nice place to spend a night in the park enjoying some delicious food.

Staff: Attentive, friendly, and most importantly, chill. No issues getting someone to take our orders. Refillable drinks are refilled very timely. Just very nice people in general.

The only reason I'm not giving 5 stars was because the online menu was a disappointment.
For a restaurant with such enjoyable delicacies, the new menu decided to go with the standard izakaya style of having NO PICTURES.
Your food is great, and your menu is digital, so why not take a few photos (or grab some of the amazing ones here) and put that on your DIGITAL menu?
Maybe not for the drinks but definitely the food and the desserts. You have nothing to be ashamed about your food, so build a little anticipation and excitement for us by putting some nice photos of the food in your menu! I feel it's especially important for first-timers to this wonderful restaurant.

Nice selection of food. Taste of authentic korean food. The jja jiang miang taste super good unlike some places.

But I ordered wrongly. I didn't know the seafood soup got noodles too. Ended up I overflow myself and bill cost more for 1 person due to my own wrong order.

They also have free flow side dish available.

content: Quality food and good service. A reminder to make reservation before going

- wait staff don't really care for walk-in customers and were quite reluctant to give us a table despite availability
- smoking customers outdoors not enforced despite non smoking signs
- we ordered via the QR code. After 15 minutes even the drinks weren't served, i went in to ask and the order wasn't even picked up until i told them. so what's the point of the QR code?
- food tends to be served slowly even when restaurant is not busy

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Service (5/5): Good restaurant service. Prompt and welcoming. Has the standard korean small dishes and water, both refillable. Range of small dishes is not the largest, but good enough.

Food (5/5): We ordered the set A - 5 dumplings, sweet and sour pork, and choice 2x, either Jjajamyeon or Jjamppong. We got 2 Jjamppong.
The dumplings are nice, with vegetable and meat fillings, in particular, liked the sauce that comes with it. Reminds me of Xiao Long Baos.
The sweet and sour pork was great as well - the sauce was served at the side so that the pork remains crispy after some time. The sauce pairs very well with the pork.
I liked the soup of the jjamppong, and the seafood is quite plentiful. The noodles are normal to me, but the portion is huge.

Value (4.5/5): Price is not exactly cheap, but reasonable for the quality and quantity of the food.

Others: This isn't your trendy kpop kind of place, but rather relaxing, classy kind of place. One thing i picked up immediately when I entered was that they played instrumental music. Also, noticed there were quite a number of koreans in the shop.

Overall (5/5): Great food, reasonably priced. If you are in the location, worth a visit. I wouldn't mind going back for the same food, or try out new ones.
Foods nice n service good.

Service is basic. Food pricing is affordable. Order a penang fried kway teow which  taste like any other hawker centre similar food item. Order a deep fried beehoon with seafood gravy which taste nice but the deep fried bee hoon is lump together thus making it hard to chew and swallow.  The penang chendol taste nice but lack the sweetness of gula melaka. The drink I order is nutmeg and kumquat but you can skip it as it is ordinary with a mild taste not like the real drink in Penang.

Large spacious and casual sitting. Mostly excellent hokkien style dishes. The crab bee hoon and nanru pork were especially good. The three egg veg could be better; not enough of the eggs. Service was prompt for a large restaurant. They even have valet parking.
Used to love it, but feels that the standard has dropped. The meat seems over tenderizer till it doesn't taste like meat anymore. Come mainly for their Foie Gras, luckily the Foie Gras still ok.
