The service is the worst I have ever experienced, no exaggeration. The servers here act like they‚Äôre not in the service line.

1) They lied to us that there‚Äôs no wine served when we clearly saw a few tables with glasses of wine. Only when we pointed it out then they served it to us.

2) They complained numerous times to our face when we nicely asked to have our plates changed or tea refilled, which I think is quite a standard for Chinese banquet.

3) When we called for one server, she just gruffly signaled for us to ask another server and walked off.

Not worth it to hold your event here even if it‚Äôs cheap, as the service ruins it for everyone. I really wonder if the people who are giving 4 or 5 stars are their own people trying to increase their rating.

This place sits where Ren¬≤ chicken rice used to be. A hidden gem. Acceptable portions at affordable prices. My personal favourite is the black pepper pasta. If you're looking for the 'atas' fare, maybe go elsewhere. Food is served up expeditiously and whilst hot and steamy!
Don't take my word for it. Try it for yourself!

Highly recommend this. My fav is their beehoon soto, remember to add their chilli as it packs a punch! For the price I think it‚Äôs worth it as the chicken is generous üëçüèªüëçüèª My dad likes their mee rebus, their power sauce (satay sauce) inside the mee rebus broth is really power üëçüèª

Actually I ordered more dishes but I forgot to take pics haha because it's a restaurant that my family has visited for years and years. So sad that the construction has affected its business; covid19 has also ruined it further. Hope more people visit and give them some business. It's a comfortable family restaurant and the food has its standard. Go eat go eat!
Great food good price

Service was fine. We over ordered until need to dabao. Lol. Should have opted for small size instead of medium steamboat, esp there are other dishes in the order üòÖ. The 20% discount for members only on the fish steamboat. I will revisit for the steamboat, chef popiah( surprisingly good and only on certain days) and yam paste.

I am not sure if this is authentic or not cause I never tried the original one before. However I do like the foods here and enjoyable. The Nasi lemak chicken cutlet and the curry taste are really nice. The Anson special zhu Chiong fan also nice and something special compare to other Chiong fan out there. The seats are limited. Come early if you don‚Äôt wish to wait too long. Enjoy~

It's a Japanese fusion place. Food and service was great. Opted for the restaurant week menu and portions were very reasonable. They have quite a good selection of sakes available too. Place is not too big (though they do have two levels) so reservation would still be recommended.

What I love the most in din tai fung is their JA JIANG MIAN!!! don't forget to add their chilli and mix it tgt super duper yummy üòç xiaolongbao is too mainstream I mean like everyone loves it and it's a must order too.  So let's talk about other food like the century eggs and the suan cai üëç din tai fung never fail us NEVER!!
satay pork very tender juicy, but their tomyam clear soup too sour. Deep fry pork abit hard.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: White chicken smells terrible, very bland, watery. Like they microwaved a frozen chicken. Horrible. Styrofoam boxes also have a lot of holes as if they have been melted.

First time there!
The fast casual BBQ aspect of the restaurant was really unique and piqued my interest.

Service was fast and efficient üòÉ.
Within 5 mins, I went from being outside of the restaurant to receiving my order üëç

Also would like to mention belle who was patient on explaining how to order and the different types of meat

Food was delicious.üòã
Would definitely visit this place again with my friends!

The beef is not very good quality, the taw karubi is like pink color and taste like pork, comes in many small crumbs and pieces, the sauce also cannot choose your own, price is a bit high as well, however the mini salad tastes better than competitor‚Äôs. Overall it is not tasty and the meat quality is not up to expectations, I‚Äôd rather go to the other brand in Clementi mall.
Best Thai food outside of Thailand and better than much of the Thai food in Thailand too. Great price, lots of food. The green curry is fantastic.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Charbroiled chicken came at room temperature while seafood marinara sauce was abit to the watery and bland side.

I seldom post food reviews but I decide to make this my first food review because it was such a bad experience that I hope more people will know about this before visiting this restaurant.

We decided to try this restaurant recommended by ieatipostishoot. Celebrating my wife's birthday, we dined in with a large family but items offered on the menu were mostly "appetiser" size and the mains option were only beef noodles and pork chop noodles serving portion for 1 pax, there are no large family size servings options.

When we arrived the staff was rude and asked to shift our seats to make way for their robot server when our seats were already very cramp together.

The portion of dishes were pathetically small and expensive.

Braised pork slices with bun were very thinly sliced.

The Pork Chop noodle taste like dry instant noodle.

The beef noodle only have 3 small piece of meat. Definitely not worth $10 per bowl.

Fried Spring rolls were very very oily.

Steam Xiao Long Bao is quite nice and juicy but no ginger served with vinegar sauce.

No chilli sauce serve in this restaurant.

Not long after our meal we were asked to settle our bill and leave because there was another later reservation.

Overall very poor food quality and poor customer service experience for our family.

Definitely won't go back there again.
Quick and friendly service. Food quality is great...

Service could be better for a weekday lunch. Food is alright. Waitress forgotten to serve the coffee. Asking for bill is also a slow process. Assistant manager was apologetic and quick to make up for it. 5 stars for the Assistant manager.

(Translated by Google) Nice nasi lemak, especially the brain.

(Original)
Nice nasi lemak, especially otak!

I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of this meal - the salted egg crab became the best crab I have tasted (replacing the butter crab from Melben), and I expected the lobster porridge to be bland or full of MSG, but instead got hit by this umami bomb of seafood sweetness. Crab - plump and sweet, with a sauce chock full of salted egg and surprisingly light. Lobster porridge - the star is the stock - seafood sweetness that is just the right balance of sweetness, saltiness and umami - drank two bowls and no MSG reaction at all. I will definitely be back for this gem tucked in the middle of nowhere

Update: went back on a Monday and the crab was still good (a little less salted egg taste), and the lobster porridge broth was so dilute - tastes like corn more than lobster‚Ä¶and the lobster was slightly overcooked. The most disappointing dish was the hk steamed grouper - $50 but it was frozen dry overcooked fish.

I decreased this rating to three stars due to the hit and miss of the dishes, and the inconsistency.
Yummy butter chicken dish with tender meat pieces and gravy that is not too sweet! Will be back for more. Naans were also fresh.
nice zichar, friendly auntie
FOODS not bad‚Ä¶
Had the Jajangmyeon and the portion was huge. The noodles were chewy and delicious. Loved the tangy kimchi and pickles which helped to balance the meat sauce.
Delicious chicken katsu don! The stallowner is generous and gives pretty big portions. I wish he could give me some seaweed

This Thai food standard has drop after the Circuit Breaker period. Their Tom Yam Soup and Thai style fried Seafood Tong Hoon used to be very delicious now is just average. Fried seafood tong Hoon the noodle is bit soggy but at least the flavor still here, must stir in the chilli sauce which is a perfect match for this dish. Tom Yam Soup is now too milky and less spicy, lacks the herbs and lemon grass flavor in the soup.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: My favorite zi char outlet which is available in holland village and balestier. Serves Great food great price.must try the egg yolk fish skin and prawn paste chicken. Normally I will order a fish soup with milk base which boast of thick slices of fish. Many similar outlets are stingy with their fish but this chain really puts in generous portions
Terrible

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Attended a dinner function here and I must say the food standard was really good. It's located in a pretty secluded location and I have never noticed it existed until I was invited to this dinner function. There Chinese design building architecture was unique in that locality and it can be mistook as an exclusive member only premise. However, it's also a Teochew restaurant open to the public. They serve dishes like Buddha jump over the wall, king prawn with broccoli, braised abalones with shiitake mushroom and spinach, signature Yam paste with gingko nuts and etc... My favor was the yam paste, sweet and flavorful. While the building look small, it's has ample parking spaces in their basement down to B3. Parking charges was also inexpensive. Go discover the great food within this quiet location.
Ordered the smoked pastrami sandwich. Maximum value at its price point. Meat was mad tender, thoroughly enjoyed it. 10/10 reco

Me and my friends ordered the bucket naan (which comes in 4 flavours), the butter chicken, the fried cauliflower as well as the curry fish head. The food that we ordered were solid and delicious. Even the fish is fresh and really goes well with the curry and the other vegetables. The curry sauce was really rich but yet not so gelat. Would highly recommend anybody who love indian food to come to this restaurant cause it's really worth the money :)

Fish and Chip, Pork Chop, chicken cutlet you won‚Äôt go wrong. üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª
Affordable western food in AMK Central.
Sometime the waiting time can be slightly long due to their popularity.

Ordered the chilli crab and cereal prawns based on reviews I saw on Food Panda. Portions were decent though they are priced high. However, the crab and prawns was not fresh at all! It‚Äôs as though they used frozen crabs, as the meat was very dry, whilst the prawn meat was tasteless. The chilli crab gravy tasted alright. Overall disappointing. For the price paid $50/crab, you‚Äôd expect better.
Loved it! Authentic Thai flavours and reasonable prices.
The food is good but is consider expensive as compared to other Thai restaurants. First time try and find it too expensive.

Ordered sashimi platter and Su udon.
Sashimi strong taste of the fridge not the fish which indicates frozen fish not thawed properly.
Texture of sashimi is inconsistent, makes me wonder if this will be my last meal.
Wanted to have Char Kuay Teow at Great World City branch. As I am unable to digest beansprouts and requested without it, but aas told they can't do customisation. First time in history!! üòê

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Chilli prata and kottu prata were my favourites from  tonight‚Äôs dinner. Mutton dum biryani has the authentic taste too!

20171119 - seems a little overwhelming on dining times, better to plan time accordingly. When compared to taste paradise (ion orchard), the food served here is less impressive. rice skin has a tangy taste to it, not fully firm. pig organs in the porridge should be sliced thinner, else they are not cooked evenly. XO stir fry rice cake were wet and bland - could not finish. on a broad basis, it is above average but as a paradise group and price (raised) component, it does not meet the mark. service is good and attentive. 4-star at best.

After reading about Rahim's mee rebus, we made a trip there for lunch. We arrived just as the stall was about to open at 12pm. Already, the customers were queuing as they sat around the few tables in front of the stall. Somehow, each knew their place in the queue. Once the stall was ready, the customers formed into a queue.

The mee rebus was good and the portion was generous. A serving of satay peanut sauce was placed over the chicken and mee rebus. Sauce was thick enough to coat the yellow noodles. The sauce wasn't overly sweet, unlike most other mee rebus. Nice and hearty meal.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Not too busy. The soup was nice. Staff was friendly & helpful. A nice place to have dinner with friends or family.

First time trying this stall after searching google. Turns out to be quite good despite the fact that we bought take away. I believe it will taste even better if we were to eat there. Food portion was ok and not too small. Will be back again to try eating there.
Most cheapest selling food in town,food delicious n good.

A wonderful experience. From entry to end. Was attended to the moment arrive at Restaurant. As prior reservation was done, brought to the table immediately. Lucky to get a window seat!
Vast variety of food on the classice menu style. Provides an overall easy to browse pages with pictures illustrations for their popular dishes.
Food and drinks came quick. All were freshly cooked and had uts own taste, not too powerful or overpowering in spices.
Staff was attentive throughout, clears dirty dishes as and when emptied.
Will totally visit again. Good place to bring clients for a meal.

We had two consecutive bad experience at Malayan Council, both at different outlets. Didn‚Äôt want to patronise the place again after our first bad experience but since we were invited to a family‚Äôs birthday dinner, we thought ‚Äòwhy not‚Äô to giving it a second chance. Sadly, our second experience only reinforced our views on the restaurant.

The outlet at Windstedt was severely understaffed and it reflected poorly on their service. None of the staff were available to attend to us and a few other diners who, like us, have been raising our hands for some time to get their attention. My husband was directed to the counter instead when he walked up to a staff to make additional orders. He ended up going to the counter but even that, he was made to wait a good 5-10 minutes to be attended to. When we requested for our desserts to be served, the dessert plates and utensils were placed on our tables, but the cakes only came about 20 minutes later with half melted ice cream. We saw that it was already prepared on the counter but it wasn‚Äôt served to us. Extremely disappointed as the cake surprise was simply ruined by the long wait. We would like to highlight that we are not blaming the staff working that night but hope that management would look into the understaff matter seriously, especially during weekend service.

My second time here. Ordered set meals. It is good at the beginning when portion is small, pretty and fine-diningish. Signature tomatoes is unique and refreshing. Portion becomes bigger towards the end. Pork and fish are good, but there is an apparent lack of creativity in the taste and presentation. It feels the same as what you will get from a good tzi char restaurant. For a restaurant with an ambience like this, I expect more. Just when my friend and I were wondering why the last few dishes came in such big portion and mediocre presentation (and no longer fine dining-ish), the waitress delivered the final nail in the coffin with the final tofu coming in two shockingly big portion for the two of us. Nothing concise or pretty about the dish. By the time the almond tea came, it‚Äôs too late to save the day.
Great rendang and otah! Love it. Friendly staff. I love how spicy my beef rendang is. Will visit again! :)

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Food is really good and value for money. Can't go wrong with the char kway tao or salty fish fried rice. Fully recommended.

Steak lover approved! Ordered the $20 black pepper tenderloin steak in medium rare (actually like medium), thoroughly enjoyed the piece of juicy and soft steak! Pepper sauce was mild, and the steak was delicious for coffee shop standard.  Highly recommended.
Have a sweet glaze(I'm guessing it's honey) on the Lok Lok. Just taste weird. Personally not for me.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: The food is alright, pricey.. but alright. My biggest concern with this stall was the rude young man at the counter. Now I don‚Äôt expect great customer service, but neither do I expect to be treated so rudely. The gestures the young man used to rush you to return the buzzer, and the manner in which he returns you your change, it‚Äôs as though he‚Äôs angry at you for something or you owe it to him..? It really does spoil your mood when food is supposed to bring you joy, so no thanks, I‚Äôm not heading back there.
Small eatery offering delicious, home-cooked styled Japanese meals and dishes. Prices are reasonable. Just that waiting time can be a bit long during meal times
Good place for gathering n enjoying delicious food
Best oxtail stew ever! & the veggies taste so good (I don't like veggies) & the soups are not salty! My favourite dining place now. Bringing my grand-kids there for a treat.

I was quite excited to try this new Western food shop. However, I was fairly disappointed. The food was pretty tasteless. And eating the salmon felt like eating erasers. The price is pretty high too. On the bright side, the staff were all very friendly. Hope that they can improve on the standard of their food.
Photo show got veggie. But dish came without. Ordered fish n chips

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Came here more than 5 times but every single time, there will be extra 2-3 items added to our bill. It‚Äôs hard for us to remember every single item we ordered but we always order 10 items but somehow the receipt shows 13 items. At this point, it‚Äôs hard to believe that it is an honest mistake. Food is great but doubt I‚Äôll continue to support. Service wasn‚Äôt great today; all male staffs and it is obvious that the they all seemed pretty confused. Still prefer the usual female staffs who are fast and efficient and always get the orders right.

Went to enjoy the 1-for-1 kamo (duck) ramen $13.80 promotion. Service was warm and quick. Added on set A for another $4.90 - a drink, chawanmusi, 1 sushi & 1 slice of fruit & $6.90 set B same items as set A just with a tiny salad and 1 mochi. Chawanmusi and sushi were OK, the rest not worth it... kamo ramen was ok.
Tonkatsu $10.80 - crispy and came with nice sauce. Salmon belly 5 slices $11, fresh but the slices were uneven in thickness and sizes...

One of the creamiest roe, at one of the best prices for cold crab I‚Äôve ever had. For the quality to value ratio, this is easily a 5 star rating, if not because of some disappointments.

Although the other dishes were good - average, the other 2 highlights were a little disappointing. The steamed promfret (0.9kg) was perhaps a little too big so the flesh was a little bit boring. I would opt for a smaller fish for a sweeter & more tender experience. The teochew style crayfish just didn‚Äôt suit my palette, it ended tasting like eating onion fried eggs‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs ok but I wouldn‚Äôt order it again.

Overall, still a highly recommended place for casual meals!
Very good vegetarian restaurant.The food is taste good and have variety of choices.

Used to be an office go to; quality has significantly deteriorated. Brisket is chewy and dry, used to be succulent and melts in your mouth.

Disappointed, probably won't visit again.

Jan 2020
Came back to try different dishes.  My wife had the curry chicken with prata and enjoyed it. I ordered the rendang chicken nasi lemak.  The chicken was okay, but the rice was lumpy.

The grass jelly drink was a little weird tasting in that the jelly tasted a little off, but the coffee and iced lemon tea were okay.

Service was efficient.

July 2019
Pretty decent food and decor, and nice place to grab a tea or coffee. Love the buns, especially the coconut and curry ones.

Authentic Hong Kong Dim Sum restaurant.. The siew mai are very nice.. I like the carrot cakes stir-fried with XO sauce.. The carrot cakes with crispy skin and the XO sauce is not too over powering where I can still can taste the carrot cake within..

Worst customer service. The server took my son's drawing paper cos she said no drawing. Even told my son not to draw. For some reason she also didn't want to give us a fork when my wife asked for one. We even have to find a baby chair and set it up on our own even though we asked the server for a baby chair.

$4 service charge is hard to accept given the type of service we got.

Food wise, not bad.
Staff came to order for us but he was so slow working and then, curry and nam bread, chicken were not hot. It was feel disappointed.

Before ordering, I was wondering why this outlet had 2 stars, I thought it was maybe due to service so I just proceeded to order. But after eating, I now understand it‚Äôs actually the food standards. I always eat Makisan but this outlet‚Äôs sushi standards r pretty bad.. the sushi rice was like old stale rice n wasn‚Äôt pleasant and all the fried things i got such as the fried tempura enoki and baby potato chips were all soggy n not crispy etc. The sushi was also a mess everyt was falling apart :( Just a feedback for improvement! :)

Taste of the food is so-so.. Quite average.. Food served was not hot indicating that the food may be left at the kitchen for awhile be serving.

To be honest I would say that going to the zhi char stall is better.

Dang Gui duck was a tad on the sweeter side.

Overall food is normal price is high. Won't return.

10/10 best nasi lemak and one of the best lontong dishes I have ever had in my life ... environment is very comforting and brings abit of nostalgic vibe for me ... will definitely come here regularly for my breakfast and lunch

Food is not bad, quite nice actually. But for the price, portions are quite small.
Food came within 5 minutes of ordering.
Free cookies!
Please improve standard of katsu and service instead of going worse

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: 2nd time coming here. The customer service is superb but their food marination standard has dropped alittle. Will definitely be back due to their friendly approach. Keep it up! üëçüèª
Ordered the sirloin steak for medium rare, turned out to be well done... and it was very very tough. Will never go for the beef or lamb dishes again
Awesome food. Great serving. Must try Aglio Olio Pasta and their homemade coleslaw!

This place is a fake. I bought fave coupon, wanted to redeem the naan coupon and they actually told me this coupon is not valid. On top of this, the food we ate was extremely expensive. 3 small piece of kitchen cost us 6 dollars.

Overall a nice place for a family meal with a wide selection of dishes. The chocolate brownie was great but might be a bit too sweet. Had the slipper lobster aglio olio, the aglio olio was spicy and taste good but the lobster (crayfish) was tasteless and dry. Waiter wasn‚Äôt rude per se but is listless and unenthusiastic.

It opened.
Nice queueing system.
Food were great for the price.
50 min Time limit dining.
Average restaurant food you can find in NTU. Steak was bad, other food ok.

steamboat offering that is almost same as Beauty in a Pot. Price points is the same as BIAP and HDL. as we went during after peak lunch hour, it wasn't very crowded. restaurant was spacious and comfortable and ingredients are fresh. the current promotion is 30% discount for lunch until 2.30pm and 50% off from 2.31pm to 4pm. love the pork bone broth as well as cordycep flower herbal soup with mushroom.
The Auntie who took down order and serve food, she is super friendly. My Family loves her friendly character and we make like a go to makan to her shop!

55 Minutes to Serve Fried Rice

Off all the order which was served within 20-30 minutes, It took 55 minites and 4 request to expedite our order for Vegetarian Fried Rice.

While the other dishes were served, timely, it got so cold since it had to eaten along with fried rice.

Restaurant was occupied at about 60% only and 55 minutes to serve fried rice was to stretched.

Date of Visit 13-Sep, around 12:10.

The bistro is a short walk from Potong Pasir station and located at the ground level of The Venue Residences.

No crowd as i was there early.   This is an Japanese anime-themed bistro.  The wall deco and on-going screening of Demon Slayer.  Main character is Naruto.

The Crispy Pork Tonkatsu was super crispy at the outside.  Yummy max.  But the pork was a little tough.  The shredded cabbage wasn't as thin as i like it to be but it was good enough.

Food portion is good and it was neatly presented.

Follow my account and my IG: Joslovesfood for more food adventures!
Good portion of food, ordered beef steaks, serve with toasted bread, Cole slaw, bake bean, tomato, only at $13... will definitely visit again.

content: food was very nice,good location ,,‚ò∫Ô∏è‚ò∫Ô∏è‚ò∫Ô∏è‚ò∫Ô∏è

Expensive and feel not really nice. 2 of us eat dinner already $59.70
Nothing special.

Was excited to find Malaysia food court with good variety at amk hub. Unfortunately the taste can‚Äôt make it. Tried the KL fried Hokkien mee and it‚Äôs a horror. Worst noodle ever! Whole plate is super black, including the cabbage and prawns. You can‚Äôt even see/ tell they are there until you dig in (there are only very few pieces anyway) Taste is totally off!!! Anyone can fry a better plate of noodle than this!!!

The Penang prawn noodle looks more promising with the hard boiled egg, small shrimps fry in chili, sliced pork and soup with chili oil. Unfortunately the soup lacks flavour, just salty.

The apom is also disappointing, soggy with hardly any fillings. The best thing I found here is the crispy pancake. Yeah, probably the only thing worth eating here.

Well it used to be quite Good with the traditional (Malay) food but after today it seems like  Standard dropped.  But the rendang is not bad failed was the curry chicken gravy got no taste. Still a popular eating ground at Jem.  Can try to see (individually) the taste . That's why I gave a 3 star. Hopefully they improve.  Surrounding you have a NTUC / Banks are conveniently located.  Still at this stage are Crowded.

Good place for quantity only. Food quality is poor, you get what you pay for. Service attitude needs to be improved, staff were annoyed when they can‚Äôt fit the dishes on the small tables and they started stacking plates, expecting us to balance it. They also ‚Äòreminded‚Äô us about waste charge when we couldn‚Äôt bring ourselves to eat unpalatable fish with soil taste - we left behind  bones and some meat. Perhaps they expected us to finish the bones too. Will not revisit

Went there for lunch during one of the weekend. Food is nice, service is good, place is clean. A little bit on the costly but overall I will still recommend this place.

My personal liking goes to the bittergound bee hoon and the oyster mee sua.

Was at ah gu kaka wa for the first time. Tried the sour & spicy soup, la zi ji (crispy and tasty) and tomatoes scramble egg. The food was delicious and reasonable in price. The frog leg seems like a popular dish appearing on most of the diner's table. Could try them out if you are around the corner.

Affordable restaurant standard Steak $11.90 in large portions at TPY coffee shop. Good deal! üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

Super bright coffee shop, with modern reno. Seatings limited thou.

Went back in 2018, standard dropped.

Overall food is not very warm probably due to huge crowd.

Truffle French fries not very crispy, would be better if it‚Äôs double fried. No truffle taste.

Fish from Fish and chips does not look appealing, slightly pale if you look closely at the picture. Would prefer if it‚Äôs crispy type of batter.

Seafood Pizza tasted normal.

Crispy salmon is quite disappointing, small portion and tasted like those sweet and sour fish from Cai fan stall (not even tze char standard).

Malayan wings tasted normal. The restaurant even gave us one more serving as complimentary. Thank you!

Better tasting one would be Lemak Linguine. However would only recommend this for sharing otherwise is too lemak to finish it.

Lastly, we ordered one serving of cake and the restaurant kindly gave us another serving as complimentary. üëçüèªThank you!

Nice place to dine in. However food can be better.

One of the better Heng Hua food around. Been a customer for many years. Quality has been consistent so far. But it‚Äôs a small shop, and only has a few tables. So try to come earlier unless you don‚Äôt mind waiting.

The stall said 24hrs open. When there after my work around 4am with my work friends. There are 5 of us. They told us they are cleaning so we need to wait for 10mins. After 10mins of waiting they told us that the kitchen are still cleaning & told us to be back at 5am? Really dissappointed on how they managed the shop.

Awesome place to get a variety of porridge combination. This shop has a lot of unique porridge that you might not find easily elsewhere. Price wise it is also pretty cheap, the service itself is also good and fast. Overall a good place if you are craving some porridge.
This TMC has a chill vibe. It has both indoor and outdoor dining space. Food is fantastic as its other outlets. They also are capable of housing events.
Food is really nice and will recommend their chicken cutlet. The owners are really friendly people as well. Been patronising this stall since their original stall in clementi.
Good service . Food are pretty good . Personally , I like their Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ and fish .recommended to come
Been here multiple times and behold.... The taste never change! Budget eaters or those who are on a tight budget. Do come over for a full meal.
Fresh and nicely grilles food in an affordable price. But do set your expectations of the waiting time, it will be 10-15mins. Staffs are quite friendly.
Expensive but good food.

I am actually skeptical to visit them again but since my agent gave me a voucher, I'll use it.  The steak, as with my past experience, was tough and hard to cut (asked for medium).  Soup and the gravies are all too salty.  Dessert is a very small scoop of ice cream, yes the scoop is smaller than usual.  Will not visit anymore.

I love the classy and classic ambience it brings... Truly a place for a date with our love one. Abit pricey but for the quality and quantity given is worth every penny. They are so generous that they gave us a free side dish.
Food was delicious. Customer service was friendly and excellent. It was a happy experience dining here.

Really decent pan fried bun they did, juicy with not too burnt bottom, obviously can‚Äôt compare to Yang‚Äôs dumpling in Shanghai but one of a decent one in Singapore

Chicken is a 2/10, too plain taste of the sauce ( maybe expensive wine in Singapore ) and the texture of chicken  is really so so

Welcome to the WORST KFC outlet in Singapore! There is only one famous female staff that is serving and collecting payment at the same time. And you always have to wait for them to fry a new batch of chickens which takes 15 mins. The chickens are literally waiting for you to appear before they drown in the oil. There was once we waited for 45 mins for them to fry 3 batches of chickens. Mine came at the third batches. NTU KFC always doesn't have new menu like the others KFC. They do not have BBQ crunch chickens!
Also most of the GREAT promo codes that KFC offers doesn't include NTU KFC. And at night they only have chickens, no burgers. Good luck to the next batch of NTU students. Have fun camping in KFC for 1 hour!!!
Limited seats

Nice place for affordable brunch and good place to chill!

Went there during their weekday brunch so it was $9.90 for the mains and you can add on for the soup of the day and drinks. Food tasted quite ok given the price, though the pasta could be a bit more seasoned or flavourful at it tasted just like cream. The chicken in the pasta was instead quite salty. The sauce for the dory was quite similar to the cream pasta but i goes well and i enjoyed that.

Thumbs up for their desserts as their waffles were so good!!  The ice cream was good too and generous serving. All that for $12!

They use an online order system so you will have to order and pay online.

Overall a pleasant experience and will be back for their waffles again!!

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: 2 simple orders of kway teow goreng. Mee hoon goreng, i waited for 30mins. No crowd whatsoever. Not the first time. Multiple times. Waste my time sia l. Might as well i cook myself. Not recommended.
Very well priced western food with promo deals.. Liked the quality of food for that price.

(Translated by Google) Delicious Japanese set meal, not too expensive

The satay sauce is nice. Variety available is not really attractive. Dont go for sell BBQ. The stall and do for you. It's much better. üòä
They kindly friendly, the food very nice‚Ä¶.the most is garlic pork belly slice, that is the most nice and delicious. I will provide bring a lot friend come to eat‚Ä¶try support them
The food are nice especially the fish. Very authentic Thai food taste. Serving is fast and waiters are polite. Recommended.
Very fresh food, good portions and reasonable price. Totally worth it!

Apart from the sincerity of a few service staff like Catherine, there‚Äôs nothing to laude about this place. Had a terrible dining experience at the place today. Stall - Wadori kept getting my order wrong and I had to wait 30 min for raw pork with asparagus. Had to keep getting up to get orders from multiple stall and lunch was cleared while getting another order when I‚Äôm not done with it. Apart from Catherine who was helpful in rectifying the situation, the others merely stood by. Food quality is really so-so, coupled with this kind of service - there‚Äôs really no joy dining here.
Excellent mutton Biriyani
Tried their signature curry chicken rice and it tasted amazing, will come again. I really love their decor and presentation, where tradition meets modernity.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Nice ambience for a chinese Teochew restaurant. The braised duck is my favourite. Ordered the Chinese New Year braised sea cucumber, mushroom dish which is good. And of course, the steamed lobster is fresh and so good. Will come again just for the braised duck.

TLDR; food was average, the ordering system leaves questions about its service. It has a literal pre-requisite to use a smart phone and a qr reader at this shop, which seems a little strange. A customer shouldn't have to feel conflicted by such a process to eat & order food.

Overall, the food portions are pretty standard, the taste was alright. Though upon entry i was given 2 packets of soya sauce & a packet of wasabi, as well as a QR code & a printed guide to ordering food.

While the menus work and are neatly sorted into categories (nigiri, sashimi etc.), it seems I couldn't order for more soya sauce packets nor wasabi. Everything was controlled to prevent wastage, but yet you couldnt order more? This probably explained the lack of amenities across the tables in the shop.

Ordered food was served using the "train" plate delivery system, very much akin to genki sushi's system. Though the wait for food was a little longer than expected. I ordered 3 plates initially, 2 arrived within 5 mins, but the 3rd came almost 10 mins after i was done with the first 2 items. I ordered 2 more items and it took about another 10 mins before they were served. The service overall was too slow in my opinion. I wanted to double check on ny orders but noted the store front had about 2 staff in front, whom had much to manage with waiting queues, customers paying their bills & cleaning the tables. It seems they are understaffed in their store front area.
The 3-stars dishes on the menu are indeed tasty. But the prices are steep for tze char considering the portion size.
Normal fish steamboat. Not much flavoured soup, taste more of msg. Some of serving staff are very rude.

The staffs are super unfriendly and stuck up except for that one Chinese uncle that deserves a promotion and pay raise. He is so attentive and caring, I'll so go back just to support him.

I think the management needs to review their staffs and realise who the good ones really are.

The food is not bad I wouldn't mind going back for.
Not a bad nasi padang stall. Affordable and yet tasty.
Good food, great service, already planned to come back. Lisa was very patient, helpful and informative.

Broth has mild pork broth flavor will sliced char siu gives that porky flavor.

Okay for a ramen fix if you‚Äôre eating there and priced reasonably cheap compared to ramen places.

Decent priced ramen for 11.90.

(Translated by Google) The food is really delicious, but the service on the floor is really bad. I came to consume it, not to see your faces. I wouldn‚Äôt want to come here if it wasn‚Äôt for the good food.
