restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Nice food, friendly staff. Portion also more then you can eat

It was a busy Saturday night but we could still get a table. Ordering and payment through QR code which saved the staff some time and energy. Food was served quite promptly. Was pleasantly surprised by the quality of my food. Delicious. Price is reasonable.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Excellent food. Very reasonably priced.

Very interesting place indeed. Very good services, most of thr staffs are bilingual too, even the older service staffs. Their chicken rice is very fragnant and its texture is also just for my 91 years old mother. Their steamed chicken is so tender and juicy too.

Service was good but what disappoint me is the dish. When the noodles are served, the soup was already cold where it make me loose appetite when i‚Äôm adding the additional noodle as it became hard and cold. This only happened today. Previously when I visited the shop, the dishes were served hot.
Ordered their Pork Katsu Don, it was quite disappointing. Rice was soaked in their soy sauce which tasted salty and the pork cutlet was kind of dry.
Beautiful ambience with great food as well!

The meats were tender and had some smokey flavour. My preference is the chicken. Beef was alright but I think another cut may have been better as smoked. Still quite an impressive little joint. Oysters were nice too. Overall good value for money.

Ordered  few butter naan, ordered some curry that I wanted on the menu. Whatever I ask all don‚Äôt have. Instead suggested those dishes that are at a higher price. Ridiculous and I will never ever come back this Yishun outlet. Just ruining the name of SAKUNTHALA,S.
One of my fav restaurants to go when I crave "home cooked" dishes. Good value for money. Friendly service. Pepper crab is awesome. Place is cosy. 2 thumbs up for the crew üëçüèªüëçüèª

19 May: The cafe is easily located in Toa Payoh, quite near to MRT station. Probably 5 to 7 mins walk from station. There is a promotion during lunch time by topping up $4.80 for soup and drink when ordering a main.

The soup is really awesome!! üëçüèæüëçüèæ Foods are great. I will definitely go back to try out other foods especially their desserts with my family! Price is reasonable, value for money!

21 May: I came back again with my family. We tried out more foods. The Black Mama Pork Burger is really nice! The pork is very tendered and juicy. It is really worth trying!! This round we ordered Carbonara Spaghetti, Creamy Chicken Penne, Kids Tomato Pasta, Kids Fish and Chips, Soup of the day, Waffles with 2 scoops of classic ice cream (Mint Chocolate and Caramel with nuts) and scoops of Bubble Gum flavor for kids. The waffles is crispy and milky taste~

There's no service and GST. What you see is what you pay for!
Not a good place to eat, seller is very rude cause order something and it was a last piece she gave it to other person

A surprise gem right in the middle of housing estates. Tims Restaurant & Cafe is great for family and small group gathering. A wide variety of western and Napalese food at affordable prices with korean beer and wine to complete your fine dining in the heartlands.
Really one of my favourite mala tang out there!!!! The only thing is tat BOTH outlet is so far away frm me‚Ä¶

Pretty decent and value for money food. Having read mixed reviews I decided to trust the average rating. Yes it is a small place in a neighborhood. Adjust your expectations a little, it'll be an enjoyable experience. Not saying it's a lousy place, it's a neighborhood store, don't expect putien in a mall experience. I ordered take away and it was rather busy with dine in and take aways as well. Recommended and will return again.
Always good food

My toddler's chicken rice of choice - he loves it so much he proclaims chicken rice is now his favourite food of all time.

Also, the aunties and uncles working at the restaurant who pamper him always probably are factors influencing his proclamation. üòÅ

I can literally eat from here all days weeks months and years.. The best chicken teriyaki rice and udon.. The best of the best..
(sue spc)

I am Japanese and had lunch here.
They are friendly and served a nice chicken Briyani!

The food was fair. The cold dish was good but no 'WOW' factor. The egg prawn was good but the noodle dish somewhat bland. The duck was well done but the fried chicken was quite dry IMHO. If you are planning a corporate function...it would be ideal but for a special dinner function such as wedding orba milestone birthday celebration...might want to give this  a MISS.

If you‚Äôre used to satay celup in Malacca and the lok lok vans in Malaysia, then the food here isn‚Äôt going to quite hit the mark unfortunately. The next best thing until the borders open... but not the best thing. Also opted for the buffet on a weeknight and the total bill came up to about $66 which didn‚Äôt feel worth it overall.

Shop has a great variety of Malay food, looks very legit and old school.  Nasi Lemak sold out before 1030am, so i try the Lontong.   Gravy is flavorful and serving is generous.  Missing the sweet coconut flaks and felt incomplete.  Rice cake also not the chewy type and lack texture. Vegetables also a bit overcooked and gravy is not hot as it is not kept hot in a pot but part of the Nasi Padang spread.  Had tasted better lontongs in Toa Payoh stalls.  But can eat if you like your lontong vegetables to be well cooked. Coffee from the drink stall is good though.

Will be back to try other offerings of their Malay food.
The price is slightly expensive but the staff is friendly.
Great tze char dishes to be found here. Prices are decent although it can be steep for some of the dishes. Family loves the food here. Two thumbs up.
Beautiful halal Japanese foods. Had a great time, each time. Perfect for families and very affordable.

Great experience. There was a lot of stuff on the menu that my friends and I couldn‚Äôt understand and not wanting to hog the queue, we randomly decided to order them. Uncle was very friendly and took time to ask if we knew what the bowl consisted of and explained to us üíØ Lovely service!

Ordered the Mee rebus with drumstick, bagedel and chicken satay. Portion was very generous and Mee rebus gravy was really thick flavourful (might be jelak to some), but not something I would travel all out for unless I‚Äôm in the vicinity. Chicken satay and bagedel were really nice!
Keisuke standard for Tai Hwa BCM price. Hearty broth!

Leaves a lot to be desired.. the white beehoon was the biggest let down, no taste at all... I guess if you came for the Lok Lok only it‚Äôs passable but not for the other things on the menu.. Whole family stomach feeling weird now.

As the name implies, this is more for take away than for dining in. There are a few tables inside but it is really cramped for groups more than 2 pax. Price is reasonable and standard of dim sum is better than most places - we had it dine in instead of take away. There was not a lot of take away when we were there so food was getting served about 5 mins of waiting.
Good food, value for money. Restaurant is understaffed so expect some time in waiting. YTF is slightly bland but the abacus seed and chicken are very good. Will be back again.
the Set Lunch is not bad. Portion of food is alright. Value for money. Quite a good choice to select from.

A very good lunch sans the stuffed chicken wings (cannot compare to YingThai's - lacks finesse and flavour). The food suits those with zh√≤ng k«íu w√®i (strong flavour) as it is well-seasoned but not too sweet. Especially love the baby kailan and very fresh fish.
Value for money.

Food - decent range of choices. Economy rice, Zi Char, Western. Have tried the ZiChar and the JWS western. The western is recommended.
Ambience - Coffee shop
Price - $.
Food a bit below expectations. Their main branch taste better especially the curry.

Have always had an average experience with Prata Wala whether in terms of food or service but I was very disappointed that two Fridays ago, when I wanted to eat PRATA because I was craving for it, I went to PRATA Wala and was told that "No prata" and that there's only biryani. Did not get anything, not even a drink. Why should I stay when what I wanted to eat was not available?
Food was indeed authentic and service was great :) Had a really good experience here
Foods good and not a lot of people which I like

Nice tasty and reasonably priced food, service staff rushing you to finish quickly;
Almost feels like being chased away by telling you "we want to leave the restaurant by 930pm"

They dont serve Thosai varieties, idli, rava, chapati etc. They have naan (was nice) and paal appam (total disaster - thick and flat - flour did not rise). We ordered our favorite Hot Badam Milk and we were served with a cup of diluted condensed milk with few sprinkle of badam. Very disappointing. Tasted horrible. I clarified with the waiter on this. He said they use condensed milk and not fresh milk. I returned the badam milk, but was still charged for it. Spent $46.20. Receipt No. YSN12364. Charged $3.20 for batham milk. We will never go to that place ever.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Tried their children drum briyani and butter chicken naan set. Spices were plentiful and dishes were flavorful. No service charge and GST. Teh C ice was only $1.50, same price as coffeeshop. Coffeeshop prices found in a restaurant. Definitely value for money and I'll come back again.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Excellent service and great taste. Recommend lunch menu during weekdays!

Ordered food for pick up. Came at the timing they told us to come and they didn‚Äôt have it yet. Waited for another 15 minutes but the food wasn‚Äôt ready. Had to ask them again before they realise they already packed the food but didn‚Äôt search it properly the first time. The food also became cold since it was left waiting for so long. No apologies offered as well. Really bad customer service.
Nice, thick n flavourful soup! Recommended to try out!

Portions are big n very value for money

Really like the buttered corn as very gao like those in Malaysia

Curly fries taste like MacDonald but after taste got heavy msg taste.

Chicken cutlet is indeed bland n has frozen chicken taste like other mention. Chicken chop w black pepper so so nothing special

I will come back for the corn. It‚Äôs that good.

Apparently Mr T**** L** likes to remove and delete comments from their facebook page. So i‚Äôll write my reviews here. Had dinner for pax of 5 on 21st march 7pm.
our table rejected almost every food that was served to our table because it was cold. Even the fried food, when questioned the staff say "oh fry alrdy but maybe never serve so become cold" another said " fried food is already pre-fried beforehand. once theres an order the chefs will fry again thn serve. maybe chef forget to fry and just serve like that" another said,
‚ÄúAiya u know usually chef see alot of order they just want to clear fast maybe forget‚Äù

Paid additional for the peking duck. no issue on the skin but the remaining duck meat which was served seperately after was bad. it was cold. whats worse is BEFORE the staff could ask me whats wrong he saw the duck and said this "oh i know the duck was left there for quite sometime" i will go make hot for you.

We left soon after and didnt bother to finish the duck. What was suppose to be a birthday celebration didnt turn out to be a celebration at all.
Have been here a few times and will definitely visit again! The food is really tasty and at a very good price. The staff is helpful and the service is very quick.
Plain prata is nicely crisp. Kopi is special. Waiting time is abit long. Just go in and sit, no need to queue (the queue is for takeaway).

I really love this place! Affordable and tasty Thai food. The best dish is the fish. All other dishes are yummy too such as chicken wings, fish cakes, pad Thai etc. But I'm not a big fan of their Tom yum soup... It gets crowded early. They have some seats outside and inside the restaurant.

Just tried the outlet at 31 Kelantan lane
Beef is overcooked and taste like rubber.
Egg is also overcooked.
Don't deserve a $11 pricing.
Sad.
To add on
Potato is extremely Satish.
Total failure.
Thanks God.
It seems it will be last I order again.
Boss.
Please do something

Ordered the promo chilli crab & Peking duck. Both are nice but have to top up $15 to fry the duck meat with Ee Fu noodles, the fried noodle is little too salty.
The salted egg prawns are very dry and not creamy.
If there is no promotion, food items are considered pricey as the serving portions are small.
Standard dropped... different from the old thailkly at novena.

First time here and am really satisfied with their service and taste.

Hawaiian and chicken grilled pizza - üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç

Grilled chicken burger üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç
Onion rings üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç
Golden dust chicken cutlet üëçüëçüëçüëç (juiciness was missing)

If your a safra member, there's promotion and discounts. Worth it üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç

Ordered the Tom yam glass noodle soup. The soup is rich and nice but too bad they only have glass noodles.

Find the Thai ice tea so so only so can skip.

The price is not too expensive so recommend to try. Not much parking so need to park at nearby hdb instead.
Authentic thai food - enjoy the thai basil pork rice

Nice place to eat with family.
Like the quality of their sushi.
Great taste of Hot Sake...
You can eat dry Mee Siam with hot coffee here or Curry puff with coffee.  Nice.
Simple menu and friendly staff

This is my ‚Äúgo to‚Äù spot for Teh Tarik. I recently enjoyed my first Briyani Chicken Tikka. The portions are more than ample. VERY friendly service - they recall me by name! Quick service. You have the option of eating outside under shade, or in an air conditioned space. For regional muslim Indian food, I doesn‚Äôt get more authentic than this. This is one of the best ‚Äúvillage‚Äù stalls that can be found in Chinatown.
Menu items were limited, small portion, food was cold, pricey but the venue was cosy. I prefer the outlet in tekka, at least the customer service is good there.

It should be called as heart attack pasta as pasta was very very oily and cheeze on the top makes it scarier to eat. Prices definitely are not student friendly. This pasta is a health risk and and costly for the pocket.

Amazing food, every dish was superb! Would definitely come again! We ordered fish green curry, shrimp pancake 3pcs, scrambled omelette with minced pork, stir fry kai lan, Thai iced tea and a coconut shake.

Food is pretty good, prices are reasonable, and the people are friendly. Only gripe is that it gets really crowded during peak hours, and seating can be hard to come by - especially with the pandemic restrictions.
Great place to have a drink if you're on NTU's campus.

I got the baked meatball Mac & Cheese. 3 pieces of meatballs, but the meatballs were great.
The taste of the mac and cheese was not homogeneous, some parts were quite bland, maybe could do better with slightly more cheese.
Japanese food court concept. Fuss free japanese food.
The bee hoon was quite special because it was so thin. I liked the candied yam too. But the rest were about average.

Chance upon this stall selling Nasi Padang on the last row at the cheng san market and food centre. I was there around 1pm and the selection of dishes to select from was still huge. There was a short queue when i was there.

Selected 3 dishes, sambal hotdogs, egg and cabbage, paid SGD$4 for my meal. Food was pretty decent. Love the lemak chilli padi gravy, very rich and the spiciness level was alright. Portion wise, just right for me and quite value for money.

Their other dishes looks quite mouthwatering as well. I would try their other dishes next time round.
Not much customers on weekdays MD and some of the stalls are closed.
Super delicious food! Must try the Leng Sap, Steam fish and prawn glass noodle. Great service from Tai too! Must try the grilled squid too
Food is tasty!

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Taste nothing fantastic but can do, meat and chicken well cook. Pricing acceptable and some are cheap. Please don't come at lunch hours, as many offices around very crowded and very hard to find a seat. After 1.45pm or before 12 noon is the best times.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Very disappointed that the staff mixed up my reservation despite calling and making the reservation 2 weeks in advance. Even called in the afternoon to confirm and the staff confirmed my request. Only to receive a call later on from an impatient staff telling me that my request was not able to be catered for. I'm disappointed by your service, hwang sil. We were looking forward to enjoying Korean food with our Korean colleagues.
Prata the best around the area, thosai also. Boss is nice.
The staff is always ready to help,I love the atmosphere cossy the foods delicious and beautifuly preented.

One of the best mee rebus and satay I ever had. Mee rebus(power) is really good. The portion is really generous. The chicken satay is also really good. They only use chicken thigh meat. Every bite of the chicken satay is tender and juicy. If you like satay kajang in Malaysia, you will definitely like this one too. Going to try their mutton satay on my next visit because they don't have it today. - Satay only available after 3pm.
Mala fans must come here to try, but food abit salty, rmb to request less salty
Very small portions

After the opening craze calm down, we manage to dine in for dinner. Food was alright, service is prompt and the sushi train is cute üòÅ only downside it can be abit pricey, but im guessing the recent inflation cost went up too. ( so minus 1star)

The fries was surprisingly not bad. Maybe will come once in a looong time.
Good food, great service... Even our children like the dishes we ordered.
I love Curry Times. Traditional old-school food done well. Pardon the photos of half-eaten food. Too yummy to wait before digging in.
Affordable Japanese flair

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Food is good. Portion is good too
Cheap price for what you're able to eat. Taste though, although not fantastic, is fairly good considering how low the price tags are

Ordered their pad thai, tom yum soup and Thai iced milk tea for my dinner on a weekday evening. The servings were very generous and value for money. My total bill was at $20 only. My favourite dish was the pad thai, the tom yum was little too sour for my taste buds and there was lots of meat inside of it. The Thai iced milk tea tasted a little weird than the usual ones at Thai eateries.
Overall, a good and very filling dinner üòÅ

My colleague recommended me wanton mee at Malaysia Boleh Jurong Point but its too far from my house. Decided to give Amk hub a shot and wasnt disappointed.

Sei Ngan Zai Wanton mee: my colleague said the noodle is nice, not the typical egg noodle but this is not the case at Amk outlet. Regardless, I enjoyed it because charsiew has the char taste, the soup is tasty with carrot and white cabbage, wanton is savoury and springy with big chunk of pork. Cost: $4.5.

Char Kway Teow ($5/$6.5): got no cockles at all. $5 for 2 prawn and small portion, its a bit expensive.

Ban mian: so so only, the onsen egg is nice though.

Asked for a fresh prata, I told them I‚Äôll could wait . Then the staff Saw 4 customer Queued in-front of the store .. suddenly my 1 egg 1 plain is ready I ordered before them while they were not busy .. soggy prata just heated awhile .. felt so cheated ruin my Monday morning ‚Ä¶

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content:
Pathetic food. Costly dishes. Chicken average at 12 $ naans (which doesnt look to be freshly made) are at 3-4 $ each. Naan are so thin that it appears to be frozen.

Single person 1 meal, easily cost 30-40 $.

Not worth.
Food quality is very mediocre, price is more than most Indian stalls and waiting time is long. But service is friendly and above average. 3 stars is about right.
Food is quite value for money. Flavour is ok.  But dessert is disappointing
Nice restaurant. Quick service. Okay food

You need to call to order their peking duck in advance. Other dishes are just average, peking duck is not the best in sg too. But good option for less crowded and mainstream restaurant for big group dining.

-1 for the staff always asking us to top up and end up over ordering.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Extremely slow service

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Love it! It‚Äôs so easy to prepare by just popping them into a pot  and drink it! Taste wise it tasted like chicken soup very comforting! üòç

Just the typical Indian restaurant, hot ü•µ and spicy üå∂
There are two restaurants here, Italian and Indian in Singapore Science Centre.
If you are not used to or fond of eating spicy food or queuing up for food‚Ä¶better come to science centre with full stomach üòä to enjoy the exhibits.

Agree with other reviews that this restaurant is a disaster in the service. All staff ran around and didn‚Äôt reply when checking on the order. Not sure if they don‚Äôt care or just plain rude. One bowl of noodle took more than half hour.

Service was fast and efficient. The Bee Hoon quite dry and too little vegetables - 3‚òÜ. The deep fried chicken Thai style not much flavor. Just the sweet sauce to enhance the taste 2‚òÜ. Fortunately the stir fried Mustard with dried shrimp and the deep fried Tenggui Fish are the winner 5‚òÜ. Mustard is simple and crunchy. Fish is fresh and crispy.
Ordered takeaway Lor mee and fried Sliced Yam which should be good.
Nice food üòã can come...
Very good ambience. Pricey but worth the experience. Closes early else it'll be even better.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Affordable and yummy! Remember to make reservation before hand

Excellent food. Ordered premium mixed grill (lamb chop, chicken chop, pork chop) and seafood bouillabaisse. All meat from the premium mixed grill are extremely tender and juicy, even in 100% cooked / well done situation. üëç seafood bouillabaisse is tasty, seafood is fresh and tender. Must try. 11am to 5pm, weekday (except public holiday) has 20% off.
Food taste is excellent. Prices are really moderate and cheap

Their mee kia noodles nice and springy, had also tried their kway tiao and bee tai mak which are just as good. Go for their sambal belachan, a good balance of spicy, sour and salty. The rest of stuff in the soup you could tell they make their own. Definitely worth to revisit!

Food was really good! Much better than expected! Beef patty of the burger very fragrant, and chicken cutlet very well marinated! And the fried mushroom, super yummy! Definitely prefer this place over Astons! üëçüèºüëçüèºüëçüèº and very cute robot waiter ü§©

The worst genki outlet! Went to collect my takeaway orders and 3 staffs walk passed telling me to wait and I waited 10mins when for nothing as my orders are already ready on the table. Finally a waitress attend to me but she was impatient and rude! Didnt apologize and even brushed me off rudely! Supervisor was at the cashier and he saw what happened but he ignored. No wonder the rest of the staffs had poor attitude! Paid for such service really not worth it! Will never step in this outlet again!

Bought their western food, was looking at other food during the visit but the other one was not available. Preparation took quite long but the food was good. Recommended to buy from this coffee shop. However, as usual, price for western foods are a bit higher compared to the rest.

Went for team get together, booked VIP room, tried multiple dishes there, but none of them are so good except prawn and mushroom.. Last but not least, ever worst customer service, the way they respond, the way they service, much worst than the local food shop,, I think those lady serves are not getting paid correctly üòÉ
waste of money. truffle fries with no truffle and parmesan, and mixed grill meal that is the size of a kids meal. the duck was the worst, literally one drumstick that doesn't taste great
Great Authentic Thai food. Fantastic friendly service. Best price in Singapore.
Nobody eat cockles without sambal kicap. Instruction not followed. Order date: 21/03/2021. Time: 14:12. Receipt no. v8qe-8dl9. Amount: $48.19. Thumbs down for this...üëé

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Authentic Mookata meal in Toa Payoh. The price is pretty cheap for the volume we get. The ingredients are fresh and served really fast.

Comfort Food ! Love the simplicity both of the restaurant and the food. Quality is good and clean. Occasionally Chef will serve you satay and chicken wings and some happening pork strips all deep fried ! Yummy! Buffet served at $25-26 per pax, comes with free flow drinks, ice cream, coffee and also crackers! You can choose your items and just let it boil or put a white peg on the plate to note that you want them deep fried . Look for Kelly who manages e restaurant there. Totally cheerful and nice. Wish there were more outlets like these. Pure and simple everytime !

If you missed or you wanted to taste the traditional Malaysian Food, can come to this place. Similar to Malaysia Boleh serving various Malaysian & Penang food. Price slightly cheaper than in Malaysia but in SGD. üòãüòãüòã
Irresponsible and ill-mannered staffs.
Excellent taste. Staff are friendly.their curry are rice in taste. Highly recommend
Just a look at the photo and you know how inconsistent the food is. Totally not worth it and it cost just about as much as restaurant price for takeaway.
Pepper beef not bad
Fish guts no clear totally, eat very smelly
Reasonable price with good food

Terrible experience. Called to reserve, told us to walk in. Walked in, said tables are booked. Waited for table, then began painful check in experience. Food was subpar, only good thing was the view. Bread was about a week old (see photo). Charge for water, menu online prices have all been raised in restaurant. Avoidable.

Good food. I tried steamed seabass $28 , dry fish hor fun $15, homemade tofu, garlic veg, tea n coke. All food was great. Spent about 65.

They accept credit card and have baby chairs.
Love their current ÈáçÂ∫ÜÁÉ§È±º item! There's a tomato based version for those who can't take the spice, or remember to ask them to Âä†Ëæ£, if you like your dish a little more fiery!

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Good and delicious food.

Lots of choices for nasi padang and kuih but you have to be early if not you will only get the 'remainders' of whats offered.

Parking is a hassle but SWEET spot if you can get it just outside.

They open early around 7 AM. Busy from the many contract workers coming to buy their co-workers their meals for the day in the morning. So their stuff is always moving and fresh. Prata, dosai and bryani are the usual here and you cannot go wrong with them. Affordable and now even more accessible from Woodlands via the TEL. Highly recommended.

Good food at affordable prices.
Traditional old school style. Love it!

Arguably the best Chinese restaurant for foodies!! Amazing food; guaranteed to leave you and your guests satisfied and wanting to return for more.

So happy that Xi Yan has opened a new restaurant offering even more to please every diner. With the best of private dining favourites and improvised casual dining selection dishes, I was so impressed, I returned to the restaurant every week for the next 4 weeks.
To be fair, I have been a fan of Xiyan and I was delighted that with this new dining concept, I can  choose all dishes ala carte and not just Omakase - i personally prefer that accessibility.)

Here‚Äôs my die-die must try otherwise go back again list:
- Starters: Cold Okra, Century Egg Pitan Tofu and Signature Tomatoes
- Basil Wine Clams with korean glass noodles (my FAVOURITE dish. Clams preferred over the prawns since you get more from drinking the broth out of all the clam shells)
- Prawns: I‚Äôm torn between the ‚Äòlighter‚Äô Truffle Prawn with Egg White and more ‚Äòexciting‚Äô Kimchee cheese prawn
- Fish: Pomelo Fish (can never go wrong with this) and Garoupa slices with Crispy Rice in Broth (broth is amazing, a bit on the peppery side so if you have young kids, might want to ask them to go easy on pepper)
- Kagoshima Wagyu Beef  (I looooove the tangy green sauce)
- Dongbo Pork Belly Pyramid (my teenage nephews were all over this dish)
If it‚Äôs your first time there, try the Salivating Chicken. But I would try the others that are not on the casual dining menu first, especially if you have limited tummy space cos there‚Äôs really so much on the menu that needs to be gradually explored.
Once again, kudos to them, they manage to make every dish such a deliciously memorable experience.

Pretty good selection at the dim sum buffet, very friendly and helpful staff as well. Carts came around quite frequently with new dishes still warm in their steamers. Worth the money for a good gathering.

Food 7.5/10
Customer service 6/10 - just because you request chili padi and staff shows a face like you owe them money, very buay gan wan to bring it to you.
Cleanliness of the table and seat 6/10 - at least it's well positioned.

Bring tissue along as some tables have small pieces of food remains there left uncleaned.

Overall : 7/10

Super worth it by taste, price and quantity comparison.
Diced spicy chicken was super delicious and fragrant.
Sweet vinegar pork rib was a little tough but still okay.
Five spice la mian tasted much better with the chilli's available.
Pigs ears salad was amazing! Spicy, crunchy and refreshing.
Chilli wantons could have been better if they added in more chilli oil and vinegar.

Amazing service, the staff were really disciplined and responsive to our needs. Food was especially delicious, I would recommend the Mongolian spare ribs, the heavily peppered but not so overpowering taste of the sauce and crunch of the pork was absolutely delectable. I had an enjoyable late lunch with my family!

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: GOOD SERVICE üëç KUDOS TO THEIR STAFF

Some people claim that Hong Kong serves better dim sum ÁÇπÂøÉ but I personally think Singapore has the best dim sum in some restaurants!
We have not visited Mouth Restaurant Âú∞ËåÇÈ¶Ü for a few years now and decided to go for there for our late breakfast today.

The ‚Äòwok hei‚Äô Yuan Yang Hor Fun was quite flavourful and some of their dim sum dishes were superb and delicious.  The serving staff were friendly and quick in their service.

Some popular dim sum dishes include the Rainbow Har Gao, Squid Ink Char Siew Bao and Salted Egg Yolk Custard Bao ÊµÅÊ≤ôÂåÖ‚Ä¶all yummy! üëçüëçüëç
I've food poisoning from at least the poke food from the bowl. I'm in pain the whole night, having diarrhoea and vomiting. I'll not recommend this place.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Great market, with lots of good food options. Highlights include the "thunder tea rice" (vegetarian, very healthy, super tasty), "88 congee" (very close to Hong Kong style thick congee with lots of options/varieties), "ugly cupcakes" and the "fish ball and fish dumpling" stall. Highly recommend a visit to this place.

Good sushi. Decent priced. Will come back again. Has lots of items on the menu, decently priced. Has inari items on menu(most places only sell inari+rice only) they have quite a lot of options for inari. Handroll with Avocado is available as well. First time having black colored tobiko here as well.

My go to place for quality and comfort food. Standard remain consistent over the years. Love the fried rice as is full of wok hei. Special shout out to Candi for being such a bubbly and attentive server. Thanks for the wonderful dining experience and see you soon at Square 2!

First time back after a long while. Ordered the chicken chop which came with spaghetti aglio aglio. The chicken was done well but the latter was just a tad away from being cooked al dente. To be honest, it was still uncooked. The server kindly changed this for me. I asked if the chef is new - she affirmed this. Also, my daughter ordered the salmon baked pasta but she was served baked rice instead. She was ok to have this, but the staff should really be more careful. It was not as if the staff were overstretched because of the lunch crowd - we were there after half past two and there were only a few tables of diners.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Me and my group of friends were having dinner at suki suki Thai @ Toa Payoh on 26th March 2021. It was a Friday night and the restaurant seems pretty crowded. The staffs are especially short handed due to covid measures. Hock seng was very patience with us. He was very friendly throughout and guide us on how to order through the QR code. His service was very prompt too when we ordered the drinks. We had a very special night celebrating my friend birthday. He made the celebration even more memorable. Thanks hock seng for your service! Stay cheerful!

If can give negative I will choose to give -10 star.
Please don't known as Malaysia Chiak it bring shame to the local Malaysia food.

Char kuey teow- chilli wouldn't be blend in the kuey teow...You will be eating the char kuey teow like French fries where you will need to sip the kuey teow to chilli sauce for the spicy flavor.

Don't ever eat the char kuey teow...it is yucks.

Very overpriced for this range and quality. This particular branch‚Äôs food quality is exceptionally poor. Chicken is dry, venison tough, food and tea is not warm enough. Service also lacking. Disappointed. Not the usual soup restaurant standards.

ordered chicken chop spaghetti for takeaway, was informed that chicken chop was out of stock, so they recommended chicken cutlet instead. was expecting chicken cutlet spaghetti, but everything was deep fried. came with fries, bread and chicken cutlet. bread was hard as rock. i barely ate anything, aunty was rude too. never going back again.
so-so

The food and service was really good! Highly recommend to give this restaurant a try! It is part of the part of the paradise group chain of restaurants in Singapore. Cost wise it is also very affordable and won‚Äôt break the bank! Would visit again!

Once you know ppl are going to come to you no matter what, you become god.

Went in ordered Masala Puri, it was rotten and smelly and my wife across the table could make out that it was spoiled.

Informed the staff its rotten.
They took the plates no apologies .

Asked what do you want in return said poori plate. Oh that's 7$ do you want pay extra.

Dude you give me a rotten food in the first place and expect me to pay as well.
Said i dont want poori meal but just poori, i guess it was less than masala poori but didnt ask for refund.
Just had and left.

I want something veg would rather go to Green Dot or prepare myself Maggi rather than visiting here.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Service attitude was poor, after waiting for more than 30 minutes order has not arrive. Asked their staff about our order and was ignored.

Good environment. I have been to Nepal before and can vouch that the Momo served here tasted authentic. The other Nepali dishes I tried was great as well. The staff was kind enough to wipe the baby chair clean before handing it to us. Great service. Would definitely re-visit again!

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Fantastic dinner!!!

Review as a delivery rider.

Popular but Frustratingly slow.

Simply because they only start to queue the ordered item for frying WHEN the rider arrives.
Yes, queue behind all the other in-stall orders at the store. EVEN though your order came in 20-30mins ago..

So be prepared to wait more than an hour easy during peak hours..

I was greeted by a warm smile and greetings by the people working there. Love the fact that they immediately offered soy sauce and wasabi. Great service!

The wait for the food was fairly short, about 10mins. The sushi quality was abit lower compared to genki but it was cheaper! Nonetheless, the sushi was tasty!! However, you can taste the mushiness of the salmon.

The Zaru soba ( cold soba) was pretty average. They changed from serving dipping sauce and noodles to just serving you a bowl of cold soba dipped in sauce. I was pretty bummed about that :(

Lastly, the crispy salmon skin ($1.80) were really tasty and cheap! Really worth the price just for a snack. Overall a good experience, definitely bring my friends there :)
Really nice surprise to stumble upon this place. Foods yummy and reasonably price

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Had to edit this review as I was charged $3 just for a small bowl of plain rice. When I questioned, the cashier pretended that the rice came with some vegetables. This could have written off as just a misunderstanding but I was dining right in front of the cashier, two meters away! Dishonesty is not a good way to attract customers.
Great place for a wide selection for Cantonese Porridge. Always tasty and piping hot..
Food nice

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: There is only 1 pathetic female staff manning a long queue of crowd at the cashier counter, taking orders, collecting payments and assigning/bringing customers to the table. It doesn't help that she is also very slow. The rest of the staffs and manager are either walking around, chatting and idling behind the beverage counter. It's very frustrating. There should be an extra staff helping to take the orders at the cashier during peak hours. Food is good and value for money but the staffs really need to be more efficient!

Only had Henghwa Lor Beehoon for lunch. At $4.50 a pop for small serving, you get enough carbo in signature fine strand beehoon. Ingredients fresh but not generous (inflation?) Suitable for those who dont like too starchy a gravy. Unlike other eateries, they dont dunk in fried pieces of yam. So i didnt have a chance to taste it. üòÇ

Every dish is flavourful and delicious. The staff is always friendly and cheerful. The prices are also very affordable. It's definitely worth a try and also great in value. If you love Nasi Padang, you will end up being a regular customer.
Pork chop is tender and taste is still as good when it used to be at S11. Fish and chip is great too. üëç
Wide variety of Muslim halal food choices here, all reasonably priced.

Whenever I am homesick for some solid 'great quality' tex mex - I look no further than Sydney stalwart GyG.

The staff at the Novena branch are courteous, happy to take dumb questions, and exceedingly speedy with their order fulfilment.

Eating in, also a great experience (now that we can)

Overall, great outlet, great staff, five stars!
Such a nice service and happy joy of food ü•∞ü•∞ü•∞
This review is only meant for the KL Hokkien Mee and Waton Noodle. Super lousy attitude and bad service from the 2 Uncle. Avoid if you can. Really will spoil your appetite....

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
spent $19 ,  not cheap nor expensive.. but yummy.
there have BLACK vinegar with sliced ginger, sign of bone fide tim sum purveyor
Pretty normal food, genuine attitude. I seldom bother to give bad reviews.

Full review of my takeaway dinner from this quaint little store.

Pork Cutlet Fried Rice $7.90.
Super generous portion, fried rice is super fragrant, pork cutlet is large and flavorful. Good amount of eggs and abit of veges too..
Score: 8/10 for me.

Mushroom and Edamame Fried Rice $7.90.
Again, generous portion of fried rice. I was extremely surprised by the amount of vegetables, compared to the pork cutlet fried rice, the box is filled up by 20% more just by vegetables. Mushrooms had good chew and flavor, Edamame was cooked just right, and added good crunch to the rice itself.
Score: 10/10.

Ngoh Hiang $2.30:
Tastes homemade, flavor is good, not overly salty skin and meat, very good as a side.
Score: 7/10

Squid Roll $2.30:
Another surprise, the texture of the squid meat and the seasoning is spot on. No fishiness, and surprisingly super tasty.
Score: 9/10

I am most definitely coming back to try more menu items. Overall, amazing value for money and taste for something so simple.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Me & my friends visit this place at least one to two times a week. The restaurant serve very delicious north Indian food with freshly prepared chapati.  The meal contains various vegetables & non-vegetarian variety.

For spacial occasions, I love the naan & various bread varieties with butter chicken.

Deserts are also available for people who like to end their meal with sweets.
A true thai homely experience, generous servings and good food at affordable prices! my mom loves their steamed fish and pork knuckles especially and we come from the southern western region!

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
It breaks my heart to give this review. This was my favourite Indian restaurant in the west! We were so thrilled at how complete the flavours were and how authentic it was a year back. There was no question- every time we felt like having South Indian meals, it was always Anjana‚Äôs. Now they are very inconsistent. Disappointed thrice already (I know; I keep going back searching for the old flavours which brought back childhood memories). Most recent bad experience was for Tamil puthandu (new year) with curries that were still raw, veges haphazardly cooked without any flavour . I don‚Äôt think they are coping with the increasing volume of orders. They need to increase capacity, staff and not compromise on taste -this is their strength after all! We want the old Anjana back :(
From,
A die-hard fan of old Anjana
The 101 noodle is fine. Other is not as expected. The tea is terrible the cup is not for the hot tea.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content:
(Translated by Google) Unpleasant shopping experience

Have a hearty breakfast as the food looks so appetising

Visited this place on a Friday afternoon around 1 pm. Asked for a table of 5. When we were ushered inside, we had to ownself combine 3 tables to seat ourselves. No menu and order list were given to us. We had to look around for the menu and order list to write down our orders. When food arrived, there was a discrepancy in the food. We ordered the same food but one of the dishes came with missing items. Food was decent. So many fked up things in one meal. Unpleasant dining experience. And the audacity to charge service charge when we literally had to self service ourselves throughout the whole meal. Do not recommend.
Decent food, reasonable price, the Japanese boss very shy, haha. Almost visit this restaurant every week.
One of my go to places for briyani because they are generous with the rice and meat. Rice is not as fragrant as some other outlets but good enough.
Overrated. Wished I had stuck to the food court next door,  where nasi lemak taliwang has a stall.
The seafood in the Tom yum soup was not fresh and tasted so bad, that I had to give up eating. Worst thing is I was down with stomach flu right after that meal.

5pax lunch at ‰∏äÊµ∑‰∫∫ÂÆ∂ on 16.8.2022

quite below expectations from watching dr leslie tay video

kong bak pao was ok quite flavourful braise pork

ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖbelow expectations not enough soup & quite hard

Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖwas better meat & soup very tasty but the second piece much better than the first so some problems with consistency

pork fritters was nice

did not have ÈÜâÈ∏°

spring roll turn out to be the best dish..very sweet tasty fillings very crispy skin and tender fillings

egg was good too not sure worth $10.75

the 2 handmade noodles were good the
braised beef better than porküëçüèª

overall nothing great & quite expensive S$93 for the type of food we had

Way below average food serve here. Worse than my medicore cooking. Pictures speak a thousand words so i straightforward. Hot plate korean chicken is bland. Hotplate egg pork katsu overcooked. Miso soup like lukewarm hot. Saving grace for the one star is the rice. My bad for not reading review as i assume their standard will be consistent across their franchise outlet but my complacent has caused a very unhappy dinner on a weekend.
One of our favourite joints. The lamb shank just falls off the bone, I didn't even need to use my knife! We must have the emperor's fingers side every time. Wife got her usual salmon.

Good location, ample carpark. Small eatery, be prepared to queue. Wonderful aroma while waiting helps to whip up appetite. 24 hours. You have traditional pork ramen of choice or singapore inspired flavours like chilli crab, salted egg yolk and bubble tea.

Good place for your cravings quick fix.

One of the iconic western food stall in Ang Mo Kio, they used to be at the S11 coffeeshop at block  711 for quite some time before taking a short break and they are back in operations at a coffeeshop walking distance away from their previous location. Decided to check this place out since i was in Ang Mo Kio. The coffeeshop was packed with people and it wasn't easy for me to get a table.

Ordering was pretty straight forward, you will be issued a buzzer once you have paid. I ordered the chicken chop which was SGD$6.50. Food was ready in no time. Portion wise, seems quite little. My chicken chop was a little tough. It was seasoned well as certain parts tasted extremely salty.

Overall, quite disappointed with the overall experience. There are many western food stalls outside that are better in terms of quality. Dont think that it is worth the hype.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Today I ordered the food. The food is delicious. No doubt to recommend.
Order their set meal for 2 and is great value for money. Come before 6.20pm if not their reataurant is usually packed with diner.
Good quality of food esp yakitori and gyudon (beef). No extra charge !!

Food literally takes forever to come. Staff was really rude as well when i asked for orders that weren‚Äôt here. I‚Äôve visited this place several times and i never get good service here. Either my food takes very long, i ask for my food and i get bad attitude from staff or they just take forever to sit me down at my table even when there isn‚Äôt a lot of people. Worst sushi place ever.. Never coming back again.
Super affordable western food with almost always long q. But they are so efficient that the wait is never arduously long.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Authentic teochew dishes. Refined dishes. Worth a visit.

Lovely place for grilled food. I recommend their Signature Grilled Chicken Diablo with Demi Glace. It usually comes with salad and normal fries for the 2 sides.

The owner let me try the Dirty Fries ‚Äî fries with parmesan, nacho cheese and teriyaki sauce. I must say the triple combo is satisfying. Besides that, the chicken is well grilled and the balsamic vinegar is pretty good. I like the fact that I could ask them to separate the balsamic vinegar from the chicken.

Last of all, the salad is fine. It‚Äôs better than the generic coleslaw with that all too familiar factory-made sauce. The fresh vegetables delight me!

I will come again for sure. I want to try their pizza.

We made a reservation after watching a video review that said the food was better than DTF and what you could get in Shanghai. We ordered xiaolongbao, shengjianbao, kongbabao, pickled cabbage roll, fried pumpkin cake, jiuniangwanzi.

Food was subpar for the price paid. Amount of meat in kongbabao was miserly and thinly sliced. Xiaolongbao and shengjianbao had way too much MSG, so much so that it hit us on the first bite.

You would do much better going to crystal jade or DTF.

Enjoyed the affordably priced meal and sides. I also appreciate the self ordering machine that mimics the Japanese style.

Place is a bit cramped though, and the table looks like it can fit at most 4 people.

very friendly and kind staff who made us feel welcomed despite running a full house. gave our little one free balloon, a princess toy and even Complimentary desserts. food was awesome as always and service was speedy.

Great food and service! The man (perhaps the owner) was very helpful and provided tissues when we were done.

Will certainly recommend
Good service and very very affordable... its yummy food

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
A first try and I am hooked. I saw the lady give the chicken wing with a chop and it made it so easy to savour it.
There was effort in sprinkling the chicken with very delicious crumbs.
The gravy from the fish curry had a unique scent. The fish was fresh without the fishy odour.
Next time I could do with a bigger portion of nasi.
Going there after 2pm will be easy for my ears as I believe that this is a popular joint

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: most dishes we tried are pretty good. except the price. but then it's crystal jade so price is not expected to be friendly. The staffs however are. The cold chicken dish is surprisingly good. The prawn paste fried chicken didn't seem to blend well with the other dishes having too strong prawny smell. overall it's a good meal, but likely to visit again when strike 4D, or it's a company event.
Good food, worth the journey there üòã

This was really a very busy during day time. Since i webt there evening, therw was no queue at all. It was quire free, got my orders very quickly. You will have a very hufe dining area, so finding a seat will not be an issue.

Nice little restaurant at Toa Payoh. They seem to have a good crowd during dinner time. There wasn‚Äôt any queue when I got there around 7pm and there was a table available soon. The food is tasty but the portion is too small for a main. Service is excellent and the stuffs are all polite to the customers.
The dinner was wonderful. Service was excellent too.
Very tasty and best nasi lemak I‚Äôve had.
We got outdoor seat for dinner, chill and greenery environment. Great food and service, recommend for family or friends casual dining.

This outlet is less busy than the other one i typically visit at bukit timah. They serve the prata and curry rather than having to self service.  No service charge. The portion is good size. My spouse and i redeemed lazada vouchers with ease. Is a good deal with the vouchers. Satisfying singaporean style breakfast. Sinfully Gratifying. The egg prata is huge, delicious and crispy like a biscuit.

Waited 20 mins to get rice and ready made dishes which are already available at the counter. Ridiculous service. Four five staff standing behind counter laughing and taking to each other. How long does it take to put something on a plate which is already ready made? The staff move so slow.
There was no banana leaf when we came at 1pm on weekend day, which doesn't make sense since the shop's name is banana leaf. The butter chicken dish was so little with just a few chunks. One vege dish was sgd5, sgd5! Ridiculous pricing ! One small strawberry lassi which was diluted was sgd5.
Tried because of the review. But won't be returning again. Your service is bad, your staff is ridiculously slow, your food is overpriced and just average.

nice prata ! nice teh tarik! nice kopi chino !

recommended ! worth the calories !

Food is good and service efficient. I ordered Thai ice milk tea, iced lemongrass, basil minced pork, Beansprouts and salted egg + chye poh egg.

The only dish I find lacking is the egg. It was too oily and I felt quesy after consuming it. I had to use napkin to soak up some oil and the napkin was soaked through.

Everything else was very yummy.
Quiet place serving decent western food at affordable price. Attentive staffs.

This place is still around after so many years.
So much history so much memory on this place. Goes to show the food is still worth coming back for. The current owner took over, without changing the menus. International Plaza has been thru so much revamp, but this restaurant, the taste is still great as ever. The chicken, beef was really good. The current service staff is so polite & attentive. Give it a try if you are in the vicinity.
Run by a Thai couple, business seems good. Ordered the pad Thai for $5.50, and it has ketchup sauce instead of usual soy sauce. Will try others next time.
Hands down the best home-cooked northern Chinese food you can find in SG. And they just reopened!
They serve southern indian cuisine. There is room for improvement for some sotong dishes they serve. Other then that, it was average it's difficult to sustain consistency in F&B line

We accidentally ordered a chef recommended cold udon, with sesame dressing. It tasted weird, we did not like it. Sea urchin was not that fresh. The beef Don could not compare with average restaurants out there. The only decent dish we had was the sashimi.

Perhaps these few dishes cannot justify this restaurant's standard. Because it is very popular among locals, we had to queue for our seat. And other customers that ordered their bento sets seemed to enjoy their food. However, do avoid the dishes we ordered as they weren't pleasant.
Service is good food even better. Might get crowded at night
Nice food, but kinda ex..

First i need to be remark!! This is my first time for the review..i will nvr put reviews as im a very lazy person!! but this is the worst experience i had at this restuarant..wrong order then insisted the order is correct! I order sword fish but send tuna and tell me this is sword fish. Hello!! Im not first time eating sword fish lo!! Lol! The staff lack of experience and training..and the food is don worth the money..sashimi not fresh.. and the worse age dashi tofu serve in the restaurant!! No taste at all ..im like eating the plain tofu instead!! First time and my last time..thank you for spoiled my lunch!
Nice open air ambience. Big restaurant with lots of dining space by the pond. Food prices are restaurant style steep. Food quality is alright.

Only one staff saved this place with his great service. Other than that service was HORRIBLY slow as they are terribly understaffed. Waited for nearly 1hr for my food in total and the food quality is not worth it all. Definitely will avoid this place.

Food is horrible especially for its price.Unagi don tasted so horrible and ramen was just salt.Never come to this place.Not a picky eater at all and will always finish food even if it‚Äôs bad but I just can‚Äôt finish it here.Goes to show how horrible the food is.Service was friendly and prompt.

The wait for the food was extremely long that is so ridiculous. I ordered a bowl of spicy salmon don, which I believe requires the least effort if you compare to the other dishes on the menu because you don't even need to cook the salmon. I waited 40 mins and when we asked about it, it seems like they forgotten about my order. I also noticed that other customers that ordered their food after us got their food much earlier than us. Seems like they don't prepare the food order by order, and more like just randomly see what order they received and prepare it first. Extremely unorganized. My colleagues ordered cheese fries as well and they only started preparing 1 HOUR after they placed the order. In the end, they had to ask for a refund because the wait is just ridiculous. Don't think I will ever come back again.
Food quality and value dont match , wont recommend to eat here. Go for Nagarathai instead!
Great food at reasonable prices. Highly recommended to try the Prawn Vermicelli and Marmite Pork Ribs.

(Translated by Google) Recommend Mother's Day set meal to send birthday peach, welcome to book

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Staff had the audacity to chase me off because he wanted to go home. We still had a pan full of chicken meat and he walked up to us with his hand gesturing he is keeping the pan right now. Was utterly disgusted by this service provided by them. Thank you for the unpleasant evening. To the people out there, there are many other mookata places with fantastic services compared to them.

It was great.

Just make sure that you do not sit at the end of the restaurant as there is a basin and tray return area. At times some dinners might gargle and spit at the basin and sitting next to it might make you feel uncomfortable.

Nice songs were being played.

I enjoyed Samosa.

I want to share my experience with the dish Masala Dosa.

I did mention to the lady cashier  that I do not take onion and garlic. She said,she does not what I am saying so I requested for another staff to speak to me.

I was told by a male staff  that there are no onions and garlic in the potato vegetable which comes along with Masala Dosa so I ordered it but I did find a few peices of onions in the potatoes when I checked so I felt bad about not being provided with correct information.

Food is good otherwise.

They must not mislead the customers but provide them with right information.
Most perfect butter chicken and naan in SG. Not 99% cooked, not 101% cooked, but 100% just nice.

Went there for dinner on a weekday night. The xiaolongbao was so-so and I don't think I would order that again.

However, the pan-fried dumplings (guo tie) were amazing! I would definitely order this again because of how juicy and tasty it was. I think I could actually finish a plate of it by myself! The guo tie is also different from the usual guo tie that I've tried from other places. It wasn't wrapped on both ends, so you have to quickly finish it in a few bites or just eat it in one shot, else the meat may slip out.

Other than these two dishes, we also ordered a bowl of noodles that seemed to be seasonal (I couldn't find the name on the menu). The pork was soft and flavourful, and the noodles were different from what I expected it to be. Usually, Chinese noodles are thinner, but the noodles that I had were thicker in size and were a bit like udon. The sauce was also on the sweeter side, and the noodles came with a huge serving of bean sprouts. Overall, this dish was not bad and the portion was alright. The food here is quite authentic and I enjoyed myself.

The staff were very fast in serving us. Also, it seems like this place is somewhat popular amongst tourists from Asian countries, because I heard quite a few people speak in Korean and Japanese.
Quaint little place at Tai Seng Centre with awesome food. Each item is prepared freshly from scratch ensuring the taste is just right. Highly recommended for a visit.

Interior looks like going to demolish
No air con
Waitress not friendly but part timer good
Preparing of food took 40mins
Food quality slightly better than ichiban
Overall 2/5 will not come back to eat again

Chirashi unagi don

We had a hearty dinner. The sweetcorn soup is nice. The meat and seafood is fresh and well marinated. There is chilli sauce and sweet sauce to go with. Price wise - value for money. Will definitely go back again.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Been a loyal customer to this restaurant for a very long time but today‚Äôs incident really question whether I would patronised the place ever again.

Was told before ordering that there was a 15% discount promotion if we sign up as member so we happily order more than usual. After ordering we were told to we can only sign up via their apps. Despite trying many many times, the app cannot register our membership. The staff told us the discount cannot be given unless we registered as member through their apps. So after so much trouble and repeated attempts, it was still unsuccessful as the apps OTP doesn‚Äôt work.  If u go to apps store page,  u can see a lot of bad comments on their apps.

In the end, we were forced to pay full price without the promised discount. Not sure it was a scam but I definitely feel cheated. It is their apps that doesn‚Äôt work, they didn‚Äôt honour their offer and we were forced to pay full price for more dishes that we normally order in anticipation of their offer. Maybe I will consider coming back when the moon turn green one day. Utterly a very disappointing experience. Thumbs down üëéüëéüëé
Affordable food and decently sized portions.

At Tunglok Teahouse, Square 2. Service staff especially Alan super friendly and attentive. Will share about the food and chat politely to my 80+ mother, making her happy. But our negative feedback is to bring back the Beef Brisket Soup Noodles, because the older folks prefer that as the meat is softer for them. Hopefully this dish can come back, as my mom really loves it.

Again, thanks to Alan for making my mom happy each time she is here. It is an experience for her.

I came for breakfast and ordered the following dim sum:
1. Vinegar pork
2. Century egg porridge
3. Steamed pork ribs
4. Steamed chicken claw

Very good service. Overall the dishes are not bad, but the price is a little on the high side.

A place where I grew up with. Definitely to see them back after closing down at the previous location. The store offer cheap and affordable western food like Chicken Chop, Fish & Chips from $6.50.

There are other food stores to check out that the kopitiam too, like the famous BCM.

Food is decent, environment chill and relax with friendly staff.
A little expensive for the food otherwise perfect

Ribeye steak is cooked just nice between rare and medium, very juicy and tender. I give high credit to its black pepper source! Kids‚Äô always like their cheesy fries, must try their cheese source! Big portion and combinations of variety of sides. Really money worth choice.
Good food!

In my personal opinion, overall experience just average. Service is a struggle during lunch with only 1 or 2 staff available for the whole restaurant. Understandable... but...

The most disappointing is the quantity of the food served. Small portion is pretty much for 1 pax. While even medium at best is 3 pax. The worse dish is the steam chicken. Priced min. at $18.80 and smallest available is only medium size, full of bones & very little meat. I have to clean the bones like a vulture so there will be meat for my lady friends. I dare to say never in my life to eat such tiny quantity at such price.

Food in pics total up to $90 for 3 pax. Sorry last min. take because trying all food with too high expectations i guess...

Other than that, overall food taste like home cook. Nothing impressive much. Perhaps great place for older folks. Most customer i see are old people. Just observations...
Buffet food are yummy and delicious.very reasonable price and good service .

Pretty long queue but the waiting time wasn't very long. Quickly ordered the food but took quite a long time to serve instead. Food was pretty decent and pratas were crispy. Ordered butter chicken but didn't expect for a full chicken thigh. The highlight and the recommended dish to order has to be the special salted egg prawn prata. So good it felt like was eating a thin crust pizza. The most expensive items ordered but well worth the price. Had a good mix of sweet and savoury pratas.
Hosted a number of dinners this week at the restaurant. Tried the ala carte as well as the set menu. Service and quality of food exceptional, wine conduct first class.

(Translated by Google) It is a famous clay pot chicken shop in the International Plaza. Weekday lunches are often lined up. The gravy chicken wrapped in cabbage goes well with rice. The omelet with the shrimp in the photo and the fried eggplant with sambal chili are also delicious.

Nice food to eat
The only reason that I visit Djitsun mall is for this restaurant haha. Love the peppery grilled chicken. Staff were polite too. Thumbs up!

Located inside Foodfare @ AMK hub. It was just on the left side of the main entrance, you couldn‚Äôt miss it.
All the items were sold in set, no option for additional items, meaning there was a possibility, you could be ordering 3 sets for 2 pax.
Service was alright. The cooking was done fast.
The taste was full of pepper and a bit hard to enjoy the food‚Äôs original flavour.
Also the stall only accepted cash, no other mode of payment.
Order yang zhou fried rice, but it served cold, and don't even bother to fried the rice with vegetable and prawn together.
Rice is very fragrant. All is good but the chicken wing seems soggy at the skin and the flesh is hard. Service is also very fast and good.
Nice claypot chicken

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Alot of tasty foods available
The prata was average. Tea no good. Can go if no other option around.

(Translated by Google) Love the food here, the owner and the proprietress are very good, the restaurant is clean and tidy!
