Easily one of the best zi char in Singapore. The food is very delicious, falvorful without being too oily or salty like most..you feel good after eating. Service is nice, and you get to sit comfortably in AC. It's not the cheapest one out there (maybe $1 more than your usualy zi char) but for the quality... I'd gladly pay the price. will come back again very soon. I highly recommend the prawn paste chicken!

The set menu has all the signature dish, all are good except the Chili Crab which was spicy with chili but not the crab source as what you expect for SG Chili Crab. Need to book during weekend dinner peak hour
worth to try the char kway that and chendol

Amazing buta don dishes served here! Recommend the pork belly and the aburi buta dishes. The unagi jyu is also a must have if you like unagi - melt in your mouth and very flavourful. Can get the mix sets for the best of both worlds - there are seasonal options and a wide variety of things other than unagi and pork, like sashimi, squid, chicken etc.

Decently priced, good location, spacious and many seats. Service can be a bit slow but otherwise satisfactory.
Love their fried lotus and potatoes! Must try their mala collegen soup with their egg as well!

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Food is good. And service i give 5 star. Speacillay lotus ...servings people nicely...
Nice dishes order by organization which for the event. Service is good. Will join next event again.

was really skepticial of this place at first due to mixed reviews on google
so came here today and tried myself!
ordered vary dishes and i think it was ok! the ramen could be salty-er because it was no taste HAHAH. so added soya sauce myself
but the chawamusui (imo) beat genki when i love eggs myself
the chawamushi was full of taste & nice!
piping hot :)
salmon was nice too
price wise is u get what u paid for! like $5 for una tama don the portion not v big but ok to share ba!

but overall is good! can come back once in awhile to try :)
went during peak hours and service prompt

Food: 3.5/5
service: 4/5

One of the best Thai food in Sg. Ordered the Tom yum seafood, sea bass, crabmeat omelette, pork belly shrimp paste and none of them disappoint us! Will definitely come back again! Service staff was very helpful too.

Dim sum buffet for $28.80++ from 3pm to 5pm

Tea included with around 30 dishes + dessert to choose from..

No need to order.. Aunty push dishes to you.. Wan how many just tell aunty..

At this price.. With nice food.. Good service..

Can come again!!

Dine in around dinner time on a weekday. It was fairly packed but the service was fast. The robot belt was super interesting!
Food quality was good! The price was reasonable.

Food quality has dropped tremendously.

1. Pork chop fried rice (pork still tender and juicy but rice is too oily)
2. XLB - Thick got thicker, less broth in the bao
3. Chicken broth - recipe has definitely changed. Tasted light with some msg.
4. Prawn wanton - fillings no longer tasty and thick skin

Service wise - super short handed though staff still friendly

Visited 19th Dec for lunch
Very tasty and price reasonable
Simply express Sushi üç£

Today's 2 Nasi Lemak was terrible, barely elidable.  All the items that came with this dish have problems...

- there was almost an entire egg shell embedded in the scrambled eggs.
- the vegetable achar were basically raw with ZERO vinegar.
- the fried chicken wing was limp and basically tasteless ... and no, I do not have COVID.

You just lost a regular customer.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: i was strolling around the neighborhood and saw upon a food in this restaurant. After sitting down, i ordered the same thing with other guest. the food was "Hor fun", this shop a bit special with a lot of beansprout and fresh fish. I liked the fish, it was fresh and easy on the mouth. recommended to come again.

Have always wanted to try this much touted stall and finally got a chance to. Gosh... Food is good but it sure is expensive! I can't believe I paid $11 for a plate of rice, beef rendang, chicken wing, and 2 vegs. One kailan and one cabbage. I honestly wasn't expecting this price tag when I was looking at the menu, as the nasi lemak cost an acceptable $6.50. My friend ordered that and added a fish, and it totaled up to $9.50 for his... $3 for sweet and sour fish slices? Totally not worth it.

But still, I thoroughly enjoyed the food.

Apart from the location, the food, portion, taste, quality and freshness.. everything is on point. Try the premium Omakase set for maximum enjoyment. Extremely worth the money. Thanks Chef Cash for serving us.
Love it, will come back again!

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Try their mock mutton briyani meal: $8.50. Generous portions of mock soy mutton and vegetable. Tasty too! I don't fancy their thosai though. Have tried it a few times; the chutney doesn't seem fresh to me.
authentic sichuan food and one spicy level is enough for me! Avoid the crowd when ordering. Lady boss is pretty :)
Great nasi lemak @ affordable price. Come before 1230pm to avoid disappointment
Great food.

3 star are for the foods only.
ordered bento set with additional add on. foods portion are full filling. salmon sushi are fresh. serving staffs are great  .. but the only downside is that the way they serve the foods. they shall serve the main course with the additional add on together ..
P/S : maybe should send the staffs for some upgrading courses ..
Food is great and portions are generous!

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Tried the green chili chicken nasi lemak. Chili is good for both the sambal & green chili ones. Rice is fragrant too. Chicken is nicely grilled but the flesh when eaten is bit mushy? Not thawed correctly? Will still return for other flavors though.
I love the nasir briyani.very tasty.staff very  friendly n serving very fast.

Miserable portion of chicken in chicken rice filled with bones. Tasted  horrible, totally not worth $7.50

Am not surprised at all with the negative reviews.. Visit at your own risk.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
The food is nice Nasi lemak and nasi sambal goreng.
I m from Tampines all the way to  upper Lebar‚Ä¶

Very good food... Specially the seafood and curry fish head.
Recommend to call and book in advanced.
Am super impressed with their service during the 2 pax limit time.
We had 2 + 1 pax that time. Lady host offered to assist to split portions equally into 2. She frequently check on us if need additional assistance.
Keep up the great service and food.
Friendly staff and amazing food! The place was also clean and hygienic! Will definitely be back again! (:
Decent bowl of ramen with gyoza. For such standards given its location in a heartland coffee shop, it is highly recommended.
Taste not bad.

The black bean sauce noodles is delightful! I enjoyed it! Kimchi is very nice!! Thankful for the complimentary barley tea. Spicy noodle taste good as well.
The korean-chinese rendition of sweet and sour pork is interesting. Heavy batter (not a fan of this) but flavourful. I wish it has more types of veg! The black fungus seems to be a bit out of place. However, the serving is too much. I wish they can provide smaller serving at a cheaper price so that patrons can consider other dishes. Halved the portion ($10-$12) will be good for 2!
I would love to come back for the spicy garlic chicken and dumplings. Price is on the higher side but the portion fits the bill. I think smaller serving with proportional price point will attract returning customers üòä

Here for a slightly late lunch at 1.00pm and we were surprised to know that the lunch time crowd just left üòÜ delighted cos we were famished!

Masala Mutton Biryani - WOW üòç the basmati rice was cooked to perfection! It was fluffy, fragrant and flavourful. We appreciate the thoughtfulness in separating of spices from the rice -  One of the "landmines" while eating briyani is to accidently crew into a cardamonü§¶ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è The mutton curry - tender and welll flavoured - had just enough spiciness to give the right amount of "kick".  Generous amounts of crispy crunchy Papadam enough for two to share üòÅ‚úåÔ∏è

Prata Volcano Chicken Steak Combo is a visual treat indeed ü§© A mind-blowing and creative twist to the standard teloh prata, along with a nicely marinated fusion chicken steak served with fries. üçóüçü

Although we were famished, the portions were huge enough for 3 to share! ü§Ø We will definitely be back to this joint for more! üòä

Enjoyed eating at this very traditional Teochew restaurant. The duck with tofu was great. Enjoyed the steam pomfret fish. Very fresh. The crawfish is good, pretty unique. The onions in it very nice. The egg with oyster nice. Their gravy has the oyster taste in it. Yam dessert was ok. Chicken was ok. The good thing is it‚Äôs super spacious. You could use some private room for karaoke as well. They serve dim sum too
One of my favourite thai restaurant. Reasonably priced and very extensive menu. Not too crowded on weekdays. Recommended.

Requested for cooked egg instead of osen egg.
This buta don is $8.90. Damn worth it!üëç

i would.say the.best thai food here, it has been for sometime never disappoint. the pricing is not cheap. the issue here is the plastic plateware. it is a shame such delicious food served not on china plateware. thats the only improvement needed. service was fast and lunch crowd build ip fast. come early

Amazing food & service was great! Would love to visit again and try other dishes! üëçüèª We liked the ambience too. Felt cozy there! They were able to accommodate to our little request as well which we very much appreciate! Keep up the good work :)
love love love! So good food and I‚Äôm so happy I found this place to get a quick thai fix anytime
Great taste.. friendly service.. Value for money

Reasonably price Thai food, large portion with slightly above average flavours. I ordered Tom yum fried rice, Kai Lan with salted fish and pork fried with basil. I find the Tom Yum fried rice lacks tom yum flavour instead it tasted more like tomatoes fried rice. The kan lan with salted fish seem to have stir-fry both ingredients separately and mix them together at the final stage. Best is the pork with basil, a bit spicy but it was good.
Chicken Briyani was super awesome. Friendly staffs and was quickly served. I have been craving for a good Indian food for awhile and this has satisfied my tummy

Their duck confit had perfectly crispy skin and mouth watering meat below, accompanied with fresh rocket and tomatoes.

The mushroom truffle gratin was also amazing from the first bite to the last, filled with creamy yumminess.

I'll back to try their pizza, burgers, and other mains!

Sorry ate too fast before I could take photos :P
Good food. Always consistent in serving and food. Love the 4 different types of sides (condiments) served when you order Thosai. Not many outlets does that. Well done.

A simple bowl of noodles. Handmade fishball and fishcake texture are great. Their Noodles not bad. And their stuffed daopok is nice. Worth a try.
But, be prepared to wait. Queue time can goes as long as 40mins.

Amazing Japanese cuisine in the west. Their dons and gyozo are a big ‚Äúmust try‚Äù dishes. Can‚Äôt complain about service, they have automated the whole process of ordering thru the QR scan method, which I find very useful. It gets a bit crowded over the weekends, so watch out for that. Would suggest ask for outdoor seating than indoors. Overall a great place to add to your list of diners

Happy to see a proper south Indian style restaurant at  Yishun area. Tried  and standard taste as in other outlets. Got good number of options to try. Good price  that matches the quality and quantity. Restaurant is overcrowded during weekends and public holidays. so there will be a waiting time. Plan accordingly. Overall good experience. Good Ambience and service.  Will visit again.

Ordered a dish that came with free mushroom soup...except that they didn't even have mushroom soup. The cashier said they would compensate me with more fries and salad. However the serving was still pretty meagre. The chicken took a long time to arrive, and I had to go back to ask about it. They then proceeded to hand me a buzzer. So I guess I had to wait a second round. Eventually the food came, chicken was ok though the sauce was good, overall I felt it wasn't worth the $7.5 though, I'd skip this and go straight for the $1.3 dim sum...there's some serious competition at this place and there's no excuse for advertising a free food item that isn't ready...how strange.

If you liked this review please hit thumbs up so more people will see it.

This place is not so much about service. A small shop located at the basement of Westegate. Ordered the Yakibuta don. I have to say, i don't really know what that was so I ordered it. It turns out to be more chewy than I like but tasty enough. The egg is done quite alright. Presentation was almost there. Maybe dont cover my runny egg with the weed? Look like like this egg needs a hair cut. ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Maybe try something else if it is your first time.

Yummy! We tried few dishes of G Cheong Fun, pig skin curry G Cheong Fun, Signature G Cheong Fun & Dry Chicken Curry Hor Fun..the G Cheong Fun is OK, the Dry Curry was great, love it ü•∞ü•∞ as for pig skin curry, the pig skin was great as for the curry, i think the coconut milk was a bit too thick. ü§§ü§§ the Signature dish was yummy üòòüòòüòò the rojak with crackers are superb üòòüòòü•∞ü•∞ heong piah was great (served warm)..coffee so-so..overall experienced is Great ü•∞ü•∞ü•∞

I don‚Äôt understand how this restaurant clocked 4.1 based on reviews. Neither the food or service is worth that much.

Came with 2 young kids in tow for lunch after a zoo outing.

I placed an order for crispy silver bait ( salted and pepper in direct translation) with less pepper sand explained that my kids don‚Äôt take spicy food. The dish was served  tossed with chopped chilli padi and rejected since the kids can‚Äôt take spicy food. Let‚Äôs take this as an oversight from the staff and move on.

The young server passed the dish to another waitress in bob hair and explained the situation. The bob hair waitress decided she need to investigate the situation and brought another 2  colleagues along to discuss. So, we had 3 persons standing at our table discussing while we were trying to have a meal. I find this behaviour to be unacceptable at a restaurant. Even busy cafes have better service standards.

The staff then tried noisily to sort it out with the kitchen which was situated 1 table away from us and separated by a folding screen. I couldn‚Äôt take it and feedback to the staff to sort out the issue quietly. The staff wasn‚Äôt able to understand my comment and brought back the bob hair waitress.

The bob hair waitress came back and defended her approach saying she needed to sort out the issue that‚Äôs why she had to look at the food order. I agreed but do it without fanfare.

She took the comment away and brought some colleagues to the folding screen to ‚Äòtalk‚Äô about my comment. The folding screen blocks view ,not noise. I can hear everything that was being discussed. It‚Äôs unprofessional. An experienced customer service staff should conduct themselves better.

The food quality is average and portions are small. Hokkien Mee was their signature dish but it was a tad too sweet for my liking. Grilled pork portion was good but really small. There was a dozen slivers and certainly not the small chunks shown in the menu. The fried fish bait was nicely fried with no hint of pepper on its second try. Restaurant was only 20% occupied when I visited.

To be fair, the younger staff were diligent in changing plates, taking orders and serving customers. If the restaurant wants to do better, more attention needs to paid to its customer service level. Hire more qualified staff to lead the restaurant. The quality of food will not be able to attract returning customers. There are also stiff competition on the same stretch of road. Lots of cafes at Brooks I and Brooks II. Parking at the restaurant is also limited. We came at 12:30 and was able to secure a lot. Carpark was full when we left at 2pm.

Future goers, receipt attached. Even a MacDonald‚Äôs meal is more worth it. ÂêÉ‰∫Ü‰∏ÄËÇöÂ≠êÊ∞îÂíåÁÅ´

I just realised the receipt was changed to reflect the order as spicy. The original food order was printed less pepper. Not a honorable move by the restaurant. If the food order never reflected less spicy elected, I‚Äôm sure the waitress would not have entertained  me when I rejected my dish.

slow service, we were told to wait for our orders in the hot afternoon sun, everyone was sweating. Order took about 10-15 mins to be ready though queue wasnt to long. Menu was rather pricy for a heartland takeaway kiosk, but sure if I will buy again. Shengkee & other dimsum/dessert  places provides better options, more choices & better value.
Great ambience and affordable food!
Great indian muslim food with friendly staff. Peaceful weekend breakfast with my prata+fish curry!

awesome mala food and thai milk tea.
luv that they fry the lotus root - its a must try!

Have been a regular customer and fan of their food here for the past 1year, but my experience today totally ruin my rating of them to the pit bottom.

Went in as usual and saw a number of customers at front tables sitting down which I assumed that they are either waiting their takeaway or some are food delivery people waiting too. So I stand at the usual spot to wait patiently for my order to be taken.

At that hour (3-4pm), its not crowded and there are empty seats and tables. Behind the counter, 1 staff is making prata and the staff whom suppose to take order is packing (what it seems like) a big order and so I waited patiently for him to be done.

Then two of the aunties initially sitting down which I stated earlier whom I assume are waiting for their orders, started taking a tray plate and picked their indian rojak along the counter area too. I didnt think much, and one of the auntie started queing n waiting beside me with her rojak.

Then the staff packing finally done, and first thing he raised his voice slightly at me "you want to order, you stand at this spot la!" while pointing to the spot behind the auntie holding the rojak. I was taken by surprised and assumed he meant I should be standing behind the auntie, so I said "but I was here very long already!"
He said "very long also have to wait what!"
He look at the auntie and asked "Who come first?"
The auntie pointed at me.
Then that staff gave an LL face and said something along "then I take your order la!" as usual with the raised voice and fierce attitude.

I was damn upset by his lousy attitude and service that I told him i"ts OK, I dont want order already!" And left.

Prata Raya, even if you have good food, with your lousy attitude to customers, you can look forward to closing down when more people like me boycott your outlet for good!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Food is reasonably priced and good. My normal go to place for a meal. However, the services (staff) could be improved. Expect a less friendly, sometimes indifferent and rude demeanor. Otherwise, okay for a simple meal.

Food was very delicious. Love the ambience. Service was excellent. Shout out to their Duxton Mary, it's the bloody Mary cocktail but way elevated served with a side of really delicious salsa-ish kind of salad where you can eat it separately or chunk everything into the cocktail and drink and still yummy!!

One of the best Indian restaurants in Singapore. I have never tasted such an authentic mutton curry and biryani in Singapore. I feel home. Their samosas are the best. I would suggest all the samosa lovers to give it a try. I have ordered food for few events at office and home from them. I had amazing comments from my colleagues and my guests. And it was under budget. Thank you guys. Wish you all the best.

A nice Indian vegetarian cuisine. A good place in Yishun to have scrumptious meal and snacks. The quality is pretty good and value for meal. Good hygiene but tad small. I had Vegetarian meals, vadai and bhatura chana in various instances. The taste was consistent and flavourful.

Went to this Happy joy restaurant yesterday night for the 2nd time with my family for the buffet alacarte. The food was nice and worth it for $39.80++ in hotel atmosphere. Restaurant was big and serving was good.There was an event held at happy joy restaurant therefore we need to wait for our 2rd round serving about 15-20mins.But it's OK,as we understand the crowds and nowadays traditional restaurant are only a few now and now things are very expensive and we are surprised that they never even increased their price.Keep it up Happy joy restaurant üòÄ

(Translated by Google) The waiting time is too long and the service attitude is too bad.

The restaurant is beautiful! It looks like a wedding venue too~ thank you for the superb customer service and I'm really thankful for the complimentary appetizer and cakes. Such a lovely and generous restaurant üíï really appreciate the gesture. The waiters were very polite and had good service too. Enjoyable dining experience ~ always a good meal at the malayan council
Had the delicious mee rebus with drumstick and asked for extra green chilli. Thick gravy. Must try!
Breakfast menu like prata, masala thosai, vadai was delicious. Dont forget their teh tarik! Only problem that their dine-in are always crowded with people. Best is take-away if you cant wait.

Went for a belated father‚Äôs day lunch at the restaurant today and met a dishonest cashier. There was supposed to be a 10% membership discount. My sis asked if the discount has been applied and the cashier said Yes. Thankfully, my sister was alert enough and asked to see the original receipt (before discount). The cashier looked uncomfortable and presented the correct receipt.

Not sure how many times unknowing customers have been scammed.

Food is decent but please check your receipt before paying.

The Sushi standard is way better than those from other competitive well known sushi rivals. Fresh, made to order, reasonable priced.
I am impressed with the ramen and udon portion size which is relatively small but they also charged it below $4, ideally enables you to have ample stomach space to still try out their other food items  in the comprehensive menu.
Will surely visit again for any sushi crave in the future.
*Given 4 stars as i think their service speed can be further improve, but might be due to the current Covid-19 situation which affected their manpower*

Loved having dinner here with my friend

Tom Yam (clear) soup was superb. Such a clean taste. The tartness was just right. The fluffy crabmeat omelette was wonderful. Enjoyed the stir fried soft shell crab too; very flavourful. Didn't like the stuffed chicken wings though. The meat was marinated well, the stuffing was a bit dry and not as well flavoured as it could be. Green curry chicken was a great portion and the gravy was thick and yummy with rice!

My favourite western food at cheap affordable prices! Their meats are always well charred and moist. I love the beef brisket the most but the last time round, the beef brisket was out of stock. Nevertheless, the chicken chop is delicious too. I especially enjoy the ratatouille as a side dish which is rarely seen in other western stalls. Will always eat again!
So so only. Don‚Äôt think will try again lor.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: My favorite place for Mookata. The place is getting packed recently and I had to queue for more than an hour to get a table. No reservations allowed.
Nice foood

Since its Phase 2 HA and we were in the area, We ordered takeaway for the Sanlou Mifen which is good and the claypot rice. Expect to wait 20min. The claypot rice is quite ordinary. Ive tasted better elsewhere but could be due to the fact that claypot rice not good for takeaway.  Across a road is a tiny mall, do shopping there.

Above the usual for a zichar place
Food was good and tasty and well portioned for its price

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Although the food is good, the service is subpar. I had a reservation for 5:30 and was informed that dinner would last 1.5 hours. After our first dish was served, it took them 40 minutes to serve the subsequent dishes. One of our dish, the steamed fish, apparently lost in the ocean. We finish our dinner by 7 o'clock even though the fish dish is making its way from the ocean.

Food were nice, Chicken was tender and juicy. Love the Coffee Pork Ribs, Claypot Taufoo was pretty good, filled with fish slices, prawns, brocoli, black fungus, mushrooms and taufoo. Love the Fish Maw Soup too! The Chicken rice was delicious which was cooked with Alchemy fibre added and was said to be lower GI.

nice place . prata is serve hot .chicken curry is nice and spicy .
a bit too pricey
Super yummy fried rice ,must try üòã.

Decent cafe food. Outdoor area is pet-friendly, no pets allowed indoors. Their chicken waffle dish is worth a try! Can get pretty crowded with family and kids during dinner hours. Overall nice ambience.

Nice old school ambience with friendly staff members.

The best dish was the piping hot claypot spring chicken, and I thought the claypot sliced garoupa was not bad as well. Both dishes went great with rice!

However, the dimsum completely fell flat of expectations and one can easily get better dimsum at most commercialized chains. The steamed coconut with egg white and peach resin was quite underwhelming, with the smell of the egg overpowering just about everything.

Had a KL da lu mian Â§ßÈôÜÈù¢ which looked very authentic when served. After i tasted it.. it was simply horrifying. I thought there was what tasted like dried shrimps inside this dark sauce noodles dish, then the staff clarified that having tons of dried solefish is part of its recipe. üôà

I have eaten many KL Â§ßÈôÜÈù¢before and non of them ever had dried solefish which taste like dried shrimps in it before. Can you imagine like having dried shrimps/solefish taste inside your dark carrot cake, dark braised trotter.

After this episode, In the future when i order this dish elsewhere, i will have to ask if they have dried solefish or shrimps inside their Â§ßÈôÜÈù¢ before i place an order. These are ingredients terrorist messing up a wonderful recipe.

Nestled on L2, this place exudes a cosy exclusive atmosphere, although it can get a mite noisy as the dining floor is rather small. Reservations necessary given the limited capacity. Good food, goes well with the extensive sake list.
Tried their Mar special mala mix mushroom. Is cold n a bit soft but still nice. Doesn't hv much 'ma', too pricey for mushroom $3.90. whras mala chicken only $3. Is this bias? üòÖ Haha..

January 24 Dinner.
If you want to come to this restaurant, please expect the following:

1. Air-con was not turned on prior to guest arrival. Guest have to remind them.
2. Dishes were served wrong and have to be reminded as well.
3. Interval of each dishes is 20 mins and food was cold when they arrived.
4. Demand payment when we are not even halfway through the dinner.

If you can meet the demands of the crowd, don't accept them in the first place. All the best to your business.
poor service, food are not serve how it looks in their menu( there is no meat in bihon) when i asked old waiter he said need additional charge for the meat...üôÑ

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: It was a feast. I think the pictures speak for themselves. The abalone deal was amazing, lots of theatre from the fire duck dish, and the sweet and sour pork in ice was a big hit with everyone. Central location at Tiong Bahru but tucked away in Link Hotel so many people don't know it's there.

Maggie soup comes with nothing not even an egg!
Fried omelette is very salty! Food is bad and expensive and services are bad! Not worth eating
And all the staff also no wear mask!

The 2nd best vegetarian food in NTU. Olive rice, broccoli, pumpkin were all very tasty. Lettuce was fresh and crispy. Overall, the food is very good and fresh. I will try the chickpeas next time. Besides pasta and potatoes, I hope there will be other options like buckwheat or quinoa in the future. Other vegs like french beans, egg plants will be good too. Just a suggestion.

Had meals here on numerous occasions. Friendly and great Thai hospitality. Some of the local food stalls need to learn from them. Have a meal is more than just good food, it means a total experience and that include service.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
This review is for the Serangoon View outlet which is not on map.

I ordered the dry char siew noodle. Discovered the noodle was submerged in a lot of chili oil which made the noodle inedible. Picture shows how much oil in the container after I separated the noodle. It was disgusting. The noodle was too oily to be consumed.

We had the ala-carte lunch buffet on 24 July. Quite good value with the birthday promo. Food is generally above average. The crabs and prawns are fresh. But the steam cod fish is not fresh as it has a weird smell and the clams have too much sand. Service is excellent especially the waitress called Ah Qing who is very attentive and can anticipate our needs. Food is served quite fast and hot. We will be back and hope they have new dishes.

The signature items are really worth a try and tastes great! It's right beside a public carpark which might be a little difficult to find space during dinner time. Must order the cabbage chicken which is sold in limited amounts daily as well as the toufu.
Long queue. Must be not bad.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
know this stall through food delivery platform.

And know that they have Dang Gui Roasted Duck.
However the Dang Gui taste is not enough.
Totally cannot Compare to Dian Xiao Er Dang Gui roasted Duck. No fight at all!
Maybe next time I will try dine in.

Roasted pork is not tender enough.

The Source Chicken ok...not bad!

Decent Japanese-style food. Visited on a weekday afternoon, didn‚Äôt have to wait long. Service was friendly and effificient. Preferred the previous version of fried salmon skin where it was thinner and crispier. I took the oyster nabe, tasted comforting and there was a surprising amount of oysters as well though there was just a few strands of Japanese vermicelli.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Happy I avoided the lunch crowd by arriving at 1115am. The food stall has been around a long time and has a string of awards and good reviews to their name. Come come. Don't miss. Parking is horrible but bear with it for the delicious nasi padang.
Prata is super nice most of the time. Teh tarik and halia are good. Often have a long wait to pay for the food, but it's worth the trouble.

Went for their buffet on a wed night, it was almost full house once they start business.

Their dishes serve decently fast once ordered through their ipad.

The prawn dumpling soup is the best for me.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Delicious, not oily, it is the first time to drink

Two person ard 90-100$ after discount. Coz portion of meat is quite small, so need to order more portions. In the end overall cost similar to other steamboat restaurants. Food is fresh. Cabbage is not good all the root side.  Generally I prefer beauty in the pot under the same group.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Menu (halal) is quite limited. Set lunch or dinner reasonably priced. Service is good though slow. Cosy ambience. Good for small gathering, family. Those without own transport may find it quite inconvenient.

We will bring our family here for dim sums, thus this will be a frequent visit for us. Glutinous rice is a mushy, flavorful rice. The crystal veg bun is fluffy and somewhat spicy. Siew Mai is a lovely. The lui Sai bun is fantastic. I enjoy their egg tarts as well, but I was unable to order egg tarts and mini Xiao long bao this time.

May 2022: This cafe has really good potential. Love the space - bright and spacious. Food was also good. Order the Cava Burger (chicken thigh) and the wild mushroom pasta. Both delicious. I liked how the cheese was melted on the bun and the mushrooms in the chicken burger. There is an option to choose wagyu meat instead of chicken for $2 additional but I read about how good the fried chicken was and hence was not about to lose this opportunity to taste it! Was happy I didn‚Äôt! Anyway, I wonder how the burger which included a slice of pineapple would taste if I had chose wagyu!

3.9 üåü for first visit experience. Their prata is dry chewy type. I like the kosong but not the egg one. The unique thing is besides the two usual curry you get (dal n fish etc), they have this nice sambal ikan bilis! It's spicy sweet. Gives the bite a different taste and texture. The dal curry also very different from those usual ones I had (some unique taste like minty which I could not figure out). I had my prata with teh tarik.. I requested for kurang kurang manis (less less sweet üòÖ). Turn out it was just nice. Staff were friendly. Generally clean. They even sell some puffs and such snacks.

Staying in yishun for 40 year and my family and relatives all stay here for over 50 year.. been buying food from syed since it open its door. But  now they abit arongant and only really serve outsider we regular they never really serve and waiting time is longer for us and also they abit stingy with the condiment and garnishes... eg cucumber sauces
Best place for budget western food in jurong west. Chicken steak and fish are the best sellers. Open till 4am. Will be great if they offer delivery.
Ordered takeout for 2 pax and was shocked to see the amount of meat was so little! SGD18 for this is ridiculous. Will definitely not visit them again.
Authentic taste! Good ambience and great value. Well recommended. Especially enjoyed the soup and fried rice, but everything is good also.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Good location for quick meal Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖ„ÄÇfriendly staff and prompt service with average food & price around $20++ per pax.
Very good quality sushi for affordable prices.
My waitress, Peggy was very friendly and helpful. She took good care if us. The food was very good and freshly made. Great place to eat ramen. Highly recommended.
Our regular Japanese restaurant in AMK HUB we love to visit that's near our home.

Bad experiences, Was seated around 6plus and ordered the foods. We waited almost 1 hour and when I asked the staff to check, she said ok checked but she didn‚Äôt come back to me. i have to walk to her and  told her that I wished to change to takeaway or else then canceled. She didn‚Äôt canceled my order and asked me to wait for take away, I asked her how long, she didn‚Äôt reply me on the waiting time just told me to wait. Again, I waited another 15 minutes. I was in the hurried to return something to someone else and I told the counter staff, I will canceled my order and left in a hurry with fuming and hungry state.  Utterly disappointed with them. Last time, the foods was served fast around 20 minutes but today I waited for an hour. Won‚Äôt go back again.  üò°üò°üò°üò°

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content:
It has become our go to place for Indian food. Stopped going Little India üòÖ
Loved chilli chicken, chicken tikka masala, kadhai chicken with naan ü´ì
The 1st stall fried osyter totally cannot make it!!!!!! Lousy

Good authentic yunan food.
Great price.
Good environment and lovely staff as in lady boss and kitchen staff.
Good location.
Located 5 mins away walking distance from novena mrt

A must visit for local Singaporeans and also a must visit for tourists transiting Singapore or visiting Singapore as tourists.

The ambience was good, but the food had some that were hits (the karaage) and some that were misses (the uni in the seafood bowl wasn't fresh - it had become a bit watery)

I think Tanoke would be a good place to come for sake (they have a wide collection) and have some of the appetisers with the sake. That I will give 5 stars. But for dinner, it falls a bit short.

It was a mother-son bonding time on Apr 2 and he wanted to have dinner here so we drove here (instead of walking) since it was drizzling.
I leave it to him to order his usual dishes as I'm easy.
We had to wait for at least 30 minutes so we walked around the mall and it was nearer our queue, they will ping us.
It has been some time since I frequent DTF and that was back in Tampines. This is my 1st time at Seletar Mall outlet and I think it is not as crowded and it looks as if the internal is more spacious as compared to the one at Tampines. Or was it because it's a late dinner, that's why...ha ha.

Had ala carte buffet dinner. Service and ambient are decent. But most of the food is cold. Signature dishes are so-so. There are many coffeeshop Tze Char taste much better than this restaurant. Totally not recommended.

The design of the stall is amazing. Food taste is superb and plenty of variety. They even have set meal for couples. Which I personally think is a good deal and good idea for those who not sure what to have. Thumb up for this place. Parking is also convenient and they also accept non cash transactions. Which is a good thing.

(Translated by Google) delicious. But full of Japanese people.

Visited in September 2021 for a family dinner. Service was prompt despite the Saturday crowd, and our orders were served quickly. Food was also as my family likes it, spicy and hot. Would recommend for family dinners or casual gatherings.

(Many of the signature dishes are from Plaza Singapura's Lokkee,  which ceased operations a while ago)

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Love steamed chicken more than roasted. Staffs are friendly and helpful.
The service by Theva and team are great. We are pleased to have a dinner here.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Tried this for the first time last month as it was the top rated food around the area. Glad to say that it lived up to its review. Staff were friendly for a hawker outlet and food was tasty but just take note the sambal chilli is very hot for those who are unable to take spicy food recommend smaller portions of chilli, it‚Äôs really spicy even for my standard and I really enjoy spicy food. Overall I would say I was blown away by how much I actually enjoyed it idk whether I was lucky I got a fresh batch but it was nice and I really enjoyed it. Thanks

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: I love this Mookataaaa! Would say this is the most wallet friendly mookata store in Singapore. Meat were well seasoned and its so tasty. Can't stop craving for their galic chicken/pork. 10 pax is only about $150 when we ate so much! However if you go there without reservation, please be prepared to queue for quite sometime. Will strongly recommend this store! 10/10

Many stalls only one staff doing cooking but they have 2 food sections. U need wait staff take turn to cook foods. Coffee is not hot  at all, most horrible coffee ever. Untrained staff? Used to a guy making coffee but today is a lady. Basic skill to make coffee minimum must be served hot!! So basic

I just had this for lunch with my family and it was not bad. It‚Äôs basically classic Mexican food and it‚Äôs good, just that we don‚Äôt particularly enjoy eating Mexican food so it was okay. The fries was good, crisp on the outside and soft in the inside. Taco was excellent, and nachos were good. Just note this, if you are thinking of getting a Burrito regular sized, know that it has a ton of beans and rice inside; portion overall very big! Service is efficient.

I want to start off by saying: generous and cooking done right!

I was actually on a hunt for good western nearby my place and happened to chance upon this hidden jewel inside this industrial area (yes its a pain to get to if you don't have a car!).

I had ordered the p1 platter combo (as shown in image) and my sides as ratatouille (yes shocking to find this on the menu in a kopitiam!) and mash potato. Not the best ratatouille i've had but its on par with your average french restaurant in singapore. Mash done right as it was creamy and smooth. Pork chop was crispy on the outside juicy on the inside with the fats perfectly cooked (which melts in your mouth if done right!). Great moist chicken with a smokey creamy sauce and finally, a BBQ glazed beef brisket. I was skeptical at first thinking it was average but this place totally caught me off guard and for $25, you can't find an alternative that gives this much food on a plate!. The chef was really nice as when I was collecting the dish he explained the different cuts off meats. The finale was when he finished the dish off by cracking peppercorns onto the main platter.

My only regrets here is that I got greedy and took a bite of everything, which caused me not to enjoy the chicken and pork as the smokiness from the brisket was overpowering. If I had to complain, the only thing would be to travel to this kopitiam. I would recommend people to drop by if you're in the area.

2 consecutive days at this TungLok for dinner. The food is good but the service is horrible.
1. Slow
2. Only 3 staff are running the whole restaurant with a manager, Zhang refused to do anything!

Believe it or not, we as customer have got to clear our own plates and piles of Bones stacking on our plates and when asked that manager Zhang (a lady) and she just refused to lift a finger!

Pity the 3 staff were running around the whole restaurant to set up table, to take order, to serve and clear table while the manager was standing like a vase!
The sambal was excellent, ingredients were fresh but the price was a bit steep considering it's located in HDB kopitiam. Take note they suka suka open, suka suka close.

Quality of food had gone down. The tomato egg dish is horrible. Price is high.... Soup is not hot and too sweet. The first 2 dishes came quite timely, the last 2 dishes were served 25 minutes later. Not a good dining experience. Not recommended.
Awesome customisable pasta joint :D. Super friendly staff, warm environment, food looks AMAZING üòäüòä

The new sushi conveyor belt concept. Very fresh Japan speed train decor. We love the conveyor belt because of the automatic delivery. The kids were having fun. It is also hygienic that the food is covered up until it reached our table. Sushi Go is very comparable to Genki Sushi in terms of concept and pricing. However, Genki Sushi's food is way much better than Sushi Go. Although the kids love Sushi Go's conveyor belt, i will still go to Genki Sushi for the nicer food.

They charge $60 and food is not delivered. The guy on phone rudely says, its not his problem, contact grab and grab does not pick up the phone. He said money can't be refunded nor they can deliver food. Can't believe such things are happening in Singapore. Just lost $60.
Good

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Order Chendol from this shop end up I only get the milk and just few Chendol . Much disappointed
Famous Nasi Lemak in Lor 7 Market... Cheap and delicious...

I like the Japanese food as it is affordable and value for money. I had rice, sweet potatoes tampora, salad, tariyaki   chicken and miso soup. Many people queue up to buy back or eat there. I tried a few times before I got to try it. Sometimes they don't open. People are enjoying it happily.
Good service, able to get some traditional penang food here at Toa Payoh Central.
Lousy service. Told to pack my takeaway bento before 1pm. At 1pm it was not prepare at all.

I ordered Teppan Black Pepper Chicken set.

The chicken came warm and the sizzling plate did not serve its purpose.

The chicken taste was bland and i‚Äôm not sure if the curry sauce was meant for this particular dish, i was not expecting it.

I ordered thru Koufu app, the food was ready after 8 mins

Interesting place for a team or company activity - The cooking is simple enough to follow but any bits of experience will help. Ingredients are prepared in such a way that the most difficult parts are already done for you.
Even though food looks good, taste wise it was okay okay. The food was pricey too.
Excellent Gado-Gado and Mee Siam
Snacks tasty n hot

This is one of the many outlets of Springleaf Prata. They always serve soft crispy prata and delicious curry. This outlet is relatively small but yet cosy. Parking is expensive unless you park at the opposite block and cross over to the restaurant. Happy dining everyone. Cheers.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: We found the BEST jjamppong here in SG! The broth was flavourful and generous portion! The noodles they used had nice textures! The tang su yuk was lacking in terms of the batter. Jjm was ok. I dabao jjm home and still not clumpy! Definitely coming back for the jjamppong!!!

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: I didn‚Äôt like the taste of chicken essence. I had to give it a try when I was pregnant. I didn‚Äôt expect it to taste so good.

First time visiting this outlet. Thankful to meet lovely service staff Ms Shannon (courteous and patient) whom assisted with our orders. Nice food and waited less.than 10.minutes for our lunch.  Pleasant experience! üëç

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
Had to wait for around 45 mins for seats as we came during the peak hour but the staff timely called us when our seats were ready.

The meats were marinated well and the vegetables tasted very fresh. Their pork collar and garlic chicken were by far the best tasting ones out of those that we ordered. It was also fairly affordable and ended up costing around $10 - 15 per pax.

Throughout our experience, the service staff there were very attentive and quick. They kept our tables clear from finished dishes and even offered to change our hot plate when he saw it was very used. Generally felt that they were rather warm and genuine as well.

ordered a prawn paste chicken and salted egg crab
prawn paste chicken is average, prawn paste taste is not strong . but chicken served hot
salted egg crab - too much butter taste , cannot taste salted egg . too much overwhelming sauce of  butter milk . crab is fresh and meat is soft and easy separate from shell

overall price- $83
Big & spacious restaurant. Staff are helpful & patient. On weekdays from 1430hrs till 1700hrs they offer 1-for-1 meals which is value for money.
Ok food for local.

Thought of celebrating Mother‚Äôs Day one week earlier, to avoid the mad rush. Booked 12.30 for 19 pax & the set to be served . However, we waited outside the restaurant for more than half an hour.. and possibly an hour if we didn‚Äôt approach them for a few times. When we told them that it is past the appointment time for 10 min, they said  ten more min . Then 20 min passed, they ignored us and we approached them again. They said another 10 min. when we showed our displeasure . There are 2 young children and a 85 year old lady waiting outside..hot and hungry. Then they said they already rushed the table of 10 who is almost done ..but they just took out their birthday cake and took lots of pictures and have not even cut cake ..means likely at least another 20 minutes to clear the table.. so means by 1.30 pm we will get our lunch..appt is 12.30.. then what‚Äôs the point of making reservation . Instead of rushing the table of guests who ‚Äúoverstayed‚Äù, they asked us to continue to wait. Asked for the manager. She said it‚Äôs like that ..just wait for a while, she started raising her voice at us when we told her not to continue to let us wait for so long, and just brushed us apart . Then she finally stormed off and returned to put us in a VIP room. Though f
One of the best mee rebus I‚Äôve ever had. If not for the above average spiciness, I‚Äôd have another plate for sure. Be sure to add on the fried chicken wings for good measure!
Best western along amk Ave 10. Whenever I have graving for western will walk from Choon boon market over here just for their western.

Nice little place tucked away in a housing estate. Quite popular given the queue before opening hours. Food prices are very reasonable and portions are acceptable for the price. Taste wise, very home cooked feel. The fried spring rolls had a unique ‚Äòwet‚Äô style filling. The Shen Jian Bao really quite nice.
Friendly staff,nice food üòã,big portion,recommended to all üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç
Velocity branch: Great place for breakfast.  Expect a queue. Local Coffee is good!
Good service & food.

Service & Ambience were fine & good.
Food portions were appallingly disappointing. Especially their Signature dish - Fish Head Curry. The size of the fish head doesn't justify for the price of $29.90++.

Curry was lacking in fullness-of-flavour - tasted diluted. Have frequented this place and enjoyed their fish head curry for many years, until today.

Hope something can be done to reinstate the quality on this Signature dish.

This is one of my tasty, authentic and value for money restaurant! My buddies and I couldn‚Äôt believe the reasonable pricing and the nostalgic taste we been missing all these years. The must try: Orh Lua, pig trotted jelly, fried caipoh Kuay Teow and caipoh egg. OMG. We going again next week! üëçüèª

Yummy authentic food!! Their mala tang was so aromatic. House chili adds great flavour to the non-spicy pork broth option. Ingredients are a bit pricey for some items (e.g. chives and beansprouts) but since those are obviously not worth it, I did not add to my DIY bowl. Other than that, portion size is big! About 4 pieces of meat for each kind of meat that you pick.
Great wokhey in the beehoon, and the crunchy rice so good. ü§©. Would give 5 star except one of our bowls dirty and needed to be replaced. 5 star food.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Quite convenient to get sundry goods. But the items in this surronding environment are a bit higher than other markets nearby. Not a bad place to hang around if free.

They changed their menu. Beef quality seems to drop.  Latte was diluted.  Service level needs to improve.
Twice i visited and they put me in one of the corner seat and forget about me. When you raised your hand, the waiters and waitresses just never seems to notice you. Pretty sad.

Uncle was friendly and the preparation was super fast! Q but waiting time was minimum. I order the highly raved Mee Rebus+ babat with bagedel which cost me $5.70. Definitely one of the best Mee Rebus in singapore!

Went to this area actually to look for something else then came across this western sounding western food stall, but manned by 2 chinese people. They were busy with orders so tried a combo n a fish plate. This is easily one of the top coffee shop style western food. Breaded fish has fish, pork is not overpowered by the usual western food sauce from other places, curly fries is not overly oily taste. The big menu makes it easy to see the dishes n order. However the ordering area is hot. It is filled with lcd screens and very hot spotlights.
Repeated visit to this restaurant for its tasty food and great service. Good food recommendations offered! Will patronise again.

My kind advice to everyone is do not order from them via foodpanda or grab delivery. For $12.30 this is what you will get. I am regular to this store and they had been generous before. Till recently they have been ripping of your money with little portion. Recently they have increased some of their food price. Which I understand due to some raw material increase in price they have to make some adjustments. But reducing the portion with higher price is daylight robbery. There must be some business ethics when running a business. Recently they have been greedy only. This will be my last order..
Amazing food quality wide choices of the Indian menu in a cozy bar cum restaurant  environment staff very friendly items ordered get delivered fast managed by very experienced operational managers.

This is the only place I don't mind steamed chicken instead of roasted chicken. The rice is very fragrant and we ended up eating many bowls. Service was good. The takeaway offer at $5.50 before gst is a good deal.
Food here is consistently good. Service staff is commendable too.

Bad service, very bad service from the lady staff by the name starting with 'S'..

Went for lunch with my mum but she was greeted and served rudely by S.

Food standard has dropped greatly. Would rather eat elsewhere.

Price wise is acceptable but I wish they could offer a no-carb option. The $4.50 option comes with 1 main + 2 sides, which the main are all carbs (Fusilli pasta, olive rice, potato). I asked if I could swap the main with some other veggies, but the answer was no from a staff in the evening (with some impatience attitude, probably tired throughout the day, let's give chance?) Feel like the swapping of main with veggie should be accepted and they should be more flexible. Anyway, the scrambled egg was super delicious.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Love coming here to chill with the family because it‚Äôs spacious and quiet, away from the crowd especially on weekends.

First time trying the la mian with chilled poached chicken Szechuan style and it‚Äôs good! Everything blend well together, have it with steamed dumplings and you have a complete meal.

The kids meal comes with a generous portion and the prawn dumplings are filled with meat fillings and prawns. Sweet potato bun is beautiful to look at and sweet too, not my kids favourite but I like it üòÇüòÇ Kids meal comes with a free drink too :)

Slightly over priced for what they are offering. Their recipes actually does not have Authentic Thai taste... It's kind of Chinese-Thai taste. Coconut milk shake is totally artificial flavored not even a single ingrident of coconut. Look out for other Thai restaurants in city if you have time...

It's a neighbourhood zi char restaurant that doesn't really stand out despite the reviews. I tried the special bee hoon and imperial pork chop rice. Special bee hoon attempted to be like white bee hoon (sembawang?) but doesn't quite make it. It's not bad but not special. Prawns were bland. Pork chop was dry and the sauce didn't have much flavor. Rice was hard and dry. OK for a neighbourhood zi char but not worth traveling for.
They pour drink first and wait for food. So I cannot get cool and fresh drinks

Food: 4* but slightly sweet for mee goreng,  others just nice.
Service: 4*
Chrysanthemums and rose tea: 4*
Location: shop just in front of the bus stop at Jalan Kayu.
Will be back again to try other foods

great food! So flavorful and tasty~ staff are so nice as well! Will come again ~
second time hereÔºÅeven better!! Shout out to the sweetest girl here ICE! So kind and pretty and beautiful and thoughtful! Oyster here is so fresh and lightly sweet, good match with the sparkling wine! Cannot go south with the price, only 2SGD each! We ordered a dozen! Happy with our full stomach! Definitely will come third time!

Unique fusion allium-free vegetarian dimsum! Would recommend the Truffle Mixed Mushroom Dumplings. Unfortunately the information I got via social media direct message, via the staff in-person, and via the online Oddle menu all differ greatly in terms of which items are vegan... Best to verify with the staff when ordering if you don't consume egg and dairy. Hope this can be better clarified. Conveniently located near Novena MRT Station Exit B.

First time ordering (saw the post in Hawkers United FB group). Ordered takeaway Kway Teow Soto, Mee Rebus and 10 sticks of chicken Satay in P2HA times - still so good even after driving home, we ate about 20 mins after purchasing. Can't wait to try when dine-in resumes.

Definitely the place to go for good jamppong and jajangmyeon. Waited for ard 30 mins to get a table on a Sunday afternoon. It was raining that time which might have resulted in a shorter queue. The noodle is really good. Jajangmyeon is almost similar to what I have tasted in Seoul. The tangsukyuk is less crispy than some other stores in Singapore, I guess it owes it to lesser batter used, but still, their tangsukyuk is pretty good too. Didn't received the 'excellent' service as many had reviewed. We were the only table not served with barley tea and finally served when asked. The table that came and ordered later than us got their food earlier than us. There was a lapse in their food hygiene - i found a strand of hair in our bowl of jajangmyeon, what an anticlimax after all that waiting to dig in. Fortunately, the staff were sincerely apologetic and replaced with a new one immediately. Definitely would go back again if i didnt find the hair in my bowl of noodles, ewww.

Have been to this cosy and authentic Shanghainese restaurant for many years.

They have a small menu but everything on it is worth the space in your stomach. The ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖ takes about 25mins from preparation to table so be sure to order in advance so the boss can time it to your arrival.

It‚Äôs a very cosy sitting of 7 tables so I never take chances with walk-ins. Always make reservations.

Definitely value for money authentic food!

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Super authentic Korean Chinese noodle place. One of the best in Singapore. Definitely going back!

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: We ordered boiled fish with sichuan pickles. The portion is huge and really fresh. Really like it

Nice ambience & cosy place for a quick bite. The curry bun is to die for. So fluffy & moist. One is not enough. Breakfast set is cheap & good. Serves traditional all time fav such as roti prata, mee curry etc. Price is reasonable.
Wang wei had provided well manners services and efficiency , food is served well and nice . The staffs here is very friendly.

Foodsssss are awesomely DELICIOUS‚Ä¶.a bit pricey but worthy every buck‚Ä¶.Ramen is so good and seafoods are perfectly cooked‚Ä¶staffs are great and place is conveniently located at Jem near the MRT. I will come back to this place again‚Ä¶üôÇ

yay to good AND affordable loklok! went tonight and whilst the queue was long, food took really quick to come. the staff there were great and polite! the broccoli tasted amazing!! :D must try their mantou as well.

Chilli Pan Mee is the stall with consistent quality. The noodle is special which is not commonly seen here, thicker but not hard. When everything tossed together, u will appreciate the overall texture and taste. Oyster omelette is not oily but sweet instead of savoury. I would prefer more crispy crust. Curry noodle is average. Claypot rice has no smoky nor charred smell. Penang prawn mee is the least favourite as taste is quite bland. We always order chendol after meal but recently the price has increased so much.

Nice, affordable thai food in Bradell neighbourhood area.
Ordered the set menu for 5 pax only $40!
Warm service as well!

This is probably one of the best western food I‚Äôve had! I ordered a chicken chop that comes with fries, baked beans and coleslaw. The chicken chop is thin, tender and flavorful and the fries are crispy. I hate coleslaws but the coleslaw here is actually good! Will come back again.

Went on a Friday evening. Ordered the Konoha Sanin set. The crispy pork Tonkatsu is perfect. Crisp on the outside and tender inside.

As for the Saba fish, they literally torched the raw saba fish infront of us till it‚Äôs cooked. But i personally still find the taste too fishy so I asked them if they could cook it longer. The lady then brought it to the kitchen and microwave it. Which after that I still find the taste fishy, and so I requested them to fried the saba fish instead which they kindly did so.

The highlight from the set is definitely the waygu where you torch each piece of the waygu to your preferred doneness. Since it was thinly sliced, I torched it to rare. I was really expecting the ‚Äúmelt-in-your-mouth‚Äù experience but unfortunately not. However I must say the waygu is still flavourful and tender.

I did not enjoyed the edamame though because I was expecting fresh edamame but they used frozen edamame instead.

Overall it was a fun, tasty and pleasant experience. Customer service is good. Price is slightly expensive. Ambience is cosy with anime themed walls. Be sure to make a reservation before going down.
I feel that to know whether a prata shop is nice or not really depend on their cheese prata standards. To me, this place feels normal only.
Good food

Very nice Seafood Marinara Spaghetti, little bit of spicy, thats what i m looking for. Love it.
Polite waitress and waiter. Clean and neat place.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Food is good but expensive, and servings are small, even for medium order. Don't ever order the Cuttlefish sauteed with XO sauce. $24 for a small serving. The cuttlefish can hardly be found, as there are few thin and small pieces, overwhelmed by the onion and bell pepper. Kailan stir-fried with dried sole fish is $24 for a small serving. Service is poor, as most of the staff are badly trained. I didn't feel satisfied.

Didn‚Äôt take photo, will do so next time and remember to ask for stronger tasting Ramen although the norm is already good enough. For $10.90, worthy dish to try though a tat expensive for coffeeshop setting.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: One of the worst of places to eat and grab a bite. Food is over priced and its so dirty

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: The taste of the chicken essence like real chicken soup. Not like the usual chicken essence i got from supermarket

An old plesant man greeted us with a smile.
Next a young chap with beared answered rudely we dont serve Thalcha when i asked. What else curry he again rudely told us to go to our table.
ALL the while both me n my friend were wearing MASK he was not wearing a MASK.
We decided to PAY n Leave without touching the food.
He must be angry with something but should not treat  customers badly.
Noticed a previous review by another Indian customer shared a similar bad treatment,
A pattern?

edit: in response to your reply-
Thank you for acknowledging my review. The first step towards making improvement is acknowledgment. Even if there are other sides to the story as you claim. I don‚Äôt think you wish for even 1 customer of your restaurant to leave with such an impression. Hopefully this will be the last time you receive such a review. Also if you were as attentive as you claim you staff would have realised we didn‚Äôt even touch our meal and the fact that it wasn‚Äôt addressed then itself and payment was accepted may be evidence enough for the lack of interest of your staff. We hope you see to this that such episodes don‚Äôt happen again.

Passed by this area, so decided to try out this Indian Muslim Restaurant since it was lunch time. Ordered Chicken Murtabak and it turned out surprisingly good. Freshly made upon order, you will get an enormous Murtabak, almost the size of an A4 paper, and it was packed with evenly spreaded scrambled eggs, onions and chicken meat. The dough which was not too thick, had a buttery fragrance which was intriguingly delicious even you eat it on its own. Reasonably priced at $6.00, I think the food was really value for money. Do give them a try, when you are around this area.
Good portion for kids. We come to the Japanese dining hall very often, each of them is delicious!

Quite a crowd when family visited on Monday morning. Although we can find seat rather quickly. The prata is ok for some of us and excellent for those who like crispy version. Ordered the plaster blaster. Quite nice if you eat together with the sweet prata

Reached this place due to a heavy rain cutting a cycling trip short. It was nearing closing hours but the auntie who served us still did it with a smile. She was also considerate enough to remind us to order drinks if we need as the coffeeshop will be closed soon.

Tried the San Lao Hor Fun and the Ee Mee. Both were very tasty.

The San Lao Hor Fun came with thick gravy. The beansprouts were crispy and the fish slices were fresh.

The Ee Mee was fragrant and enjoyable with the slightly burnt taste which is missing from so many other Zhi Char stores nowadays.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Reasonable priced and value for money. Yummy food too. But the cleanliness is a bit...... ? Went to get our own utensils and realised that the forks and spoons were all very dirty looking and stained. We asked for disposable forks and spoons instead.
The asam pedas dish is delicious, the sauce is sublime. Highly recommended
Although the porridge was ok. The staff added spinach even though we didn't ask for it and passed it off as standard
Freshly cooked food

The price is pretty affordable. Ordered the sour vegetable sliced fish soup, portion is big enough for 3 at a decent price, but the taste is normal and is not flavourful enough to go with white rice. Tried the dried wok chicken and the parts is mostly boney, suitable for older people who likes to eat on bones instead of meat. Skewer is very small in portion, not recommend to order. The pork which return to the wok is average also, I find it's not spicy enough to go with rice

This is next to Swensens, in the old wing, second floor. Great service. Most of the food we ordered came quickly. The dishes that were decent were the specialty roll, and the wakame salad. The pidan tofu was not bad. The pork cutlet was tough and hence disappointing. The chirashi don was the worst with little seasoning - just a few slices of sashimi topped on lots of rice. They don't take reservations here. Green tea is refillable. Our bill came up to $73 + for three of us.
Ordered from GrabFood and the container is filled with 75-80% chilli. Rest of it is pathetic portion of meat/veg. Stop scamming and exploiting through online orders üò°
Delicious comforting grilled fish. The non-spicy option was delightfully tasty. Need to wait abit as the restaurant can be packed at peak periods.

Bee Hoon Soto Extra Special. Extra special basically gives you a chicken drumstick instead of shredded chicken.  I have always lamented that bee hoon soto lack the meat but the option of getting a drumstick now from this stall... #shutupandtakemymoney.

The rendang is exquisite. The rest of the dishes are above average. You won't get the central kitchen type or cook-for-hire type food. All dishes are lovingly cooked by Che' Rose and her family.  However, do expect to pay more than the usual nasi padang stall for similar dishes. Enjoy :)

One of the better prata shops i patronise. The main difference is this shop sell chilli sardines to go with the pratas. Shop also provides lFREE ikan bilis sambal chilli too, short of lesser bilis nowadays(recommend that SHOP SELL the ilan bilis sambal to customers)
Very delicious food . Very friendly boss

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Yo if the dude asks you if you want this pickle side dish thing, WARNING: its $3.80. Food is decent, nothing too special.

Auntie Peggy was super friendly and she was mindful that my children and I was standing in the sun while queueing got a table. She showed us to an area under the shade outside while looking out for a table for us..her service is tip top and food was sumptuous and value for money!! This is our first time trying after seeing long queue outside always..we‚Äôll come back again! Thank you Auntie Peggy!

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
First time patronizing this stall.

Went on a weekday at 2.30pm timing. Was quite surprised to be told to wait 10 mins even though there is no queue. Food came faster then 10 minutes though. So I will expect pretty long waiting time during peak hours and on weekends.

Food wise,  taste is pretty good. Chili was not too spicy for me which is good and quantity given is good too. RIce is fragrant, Chicken is not overcooked and tastes good also.

At $6.20 is not that expensive compared to other stalls selling similar style of food.
Prata served hot, goes well with the sambal. Teh tarek power. Fish head curry so-so.
Sliced fish soup was very authentic!!! Soup tasted nice and nutritious! Price was reasonable.

Asked to top up drinks,asked 3 times never come never apologize.went cashier passed the bill with seat number n lost the bill still asked me where I sat.Told you n pointed to you where I sat 3x also still dont know.Your eyes blind or what?Never apologize too.Thats why your service will always lose to HDL.You all can only use discount to attract customers. f u.oh ya.and you all never bother to reply to complains.f u x 2

Delicious food....had their nasi padang of sweet and sour fish with brjnjals and ladies fingers during 1st visit. 2nd visit was curry fish head combo...not quite to my liking but was ok, their prawn fritters was yummy and a must have. Affordable and compatible prices, will return to try their ayam merah....and of course the prawn fritters!

Ananda Kitchen provides world class Indian Food @ The world class university NTU, the cooling restaurant located at Nanyang Technology University. NTU. Serving all kind of Vegetarian and Non Vegetarian food. Variety of foods enjoy by the different group of customers from every part of the world. It is an cool and silent locations to listen music‚Äôs and had a great meal always.

Was disappointed at first with the small space when we walked into the restaurant. We ordered Masala Dosai meal and South Indian Meal. Both sets came with tea. We had teh tarik and masala tea. The food is very good and so is the tea. We enjoyed our meal very much. The attending staffs were very courteous and helpful. The overall experience was very pleasant.
Has a very 80s look to the decor. Food isn‚Äôt bad, tastes pretty authentic. Katsu curry even had the fukujin pickles. Oyakodon also nice.

This place is mainly for their grilled food rice bowls.. The portion is adequate, though if you're hungry the portion may not be enough..so do order some side dishes to add on. Taste wise the grilled meat and vegetables taste good, with smoky taste.. There is now an expanded seating area to its left, so you can sit comfortably.. Last time we can only sit as the counter to eat..

Upon arrival at the restaurant, we were warmly welcomed by a staff, Thai. She was very smiley and friendly. The ambience was very soothing with Thai songs playing in the background. After looking at the wide variety of dishes on the menu, we decided to order the set menu for 4. The food was really good and well presented on the plates. I especially like the Thai milk tea and would bring my family and friends to try their food again.
Friendly staff paired with a sleek yet cosy environment for cooking.

I ordered oishi beef don. Totally different from picture on the menu. This is thin beef with kim chi üò§üò© felt cheated cos i really want japanese food. Cooking also took long even if I‚Äôm the only customer at 4pm.

It is our 2nd time to dine here. Tried new dishes and we like the spinach broth and yam dessert. The mala fish is a disappointment, it was served cool, not hot at all. Overall, food taste is good. Due to the crowd, staff are not as attentive.
Portin is good. Food tastes ok. Fried squid a bit too hard to chew.

The chicken here is really fantastic. Been coming back multiple times for it. The other meats, which I previously tried in the platter, were generally alright but nothing too special, with the beef brisket too fatty for my liking.

Overall, very delicious & well-presented food at a reasonable price. Quality is beyond expectation given how affordable their items are. Be sure to try their chicken!
Great service by tunglok. Food is good as always. Up to standard. Lobster porriage is very good, sweet and meaty big lobster.
The management should really look into the serving and attitude of staff. So pricey to pay $7 for this!

Really love the place. Quite n wonderful food. Looks like pte dinning. Good food, love the Truffle chick n the deep fried fish. A must try! Price slightly on the high side or mayb we the captain recommended  too many. Overall.... will go again

Nice, cozy and traditional setup restaurant to enjoy your favourite Hakka dishes and meals. Great services and fantastic dining experience. Will surely return again when craving for my favourite Hakka dishes that bring back my mum cooking and memories. üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç

Ordered the Ribeye (med rare). Done-ness  was quite spot on.

Beef quality better than some western stalls in other coffee shops.
Would like the pepper sauce to be more prominent in terms of flavor.

Price wise is on the high side but still worth a try.
So tasty and delicious. I am no expert on the dish mee rebus but here it tastes superb. I have also sampled their mutton satay which is very nice as well. The prices are extremely low.

Surprisingly good value meal at this outlet.  I like the orderly seating, serving, menu easy and special sauce choices...

The wagyu beef portion served was too fat a cut for me, i was impressed the young gentleman changed it for me. Great service. This is my 5th visit in 5 weeks.

Aburi-EN may be known for their chargrilled meat donburi bowls, but their NEXT MEATS series are flavoursome too! Decided to try their ùó°ùóòùó´ùóß ùó†ùóòùóîùóß ùó£ùóøùó≤ùó∫ùó∂ùòÇùó∫ ùóûùóÆùóøùòÇùóØùó∂ ùóóùóºùóª ùó¶ùó≤ùòÅ out of curiosity and was pleasantly surprised by how good it is. For $13.80, it comes served with 5 sizeable pieces of grilled boneless short rib glazed with their special sauce, atop a bed of fluffy Japanese rice. Grilled over binchotan charcoal, the meat slices are tender and have a nice smoky char. Tastewise, the NEXT yakiniku meat pales slightly to the other meat alternatives BB has tried thus far, but the glaze more than makes up for it with a good balance of sweetness and umami & a subtle hint of ginger. Definitely a solid meat-free option for flexitarians or vegetarians. üëçüèª‚Å£

Totally...black shop (ÈªëÂ∫ó)„ÄÇIf you notice, there is no pricing at shopfront. They keep upselling too. Take  ginger sauce also, cannot..will not return to dine here. Smallest plate is $4.50Ôºå achar dunno is they just add-on to your plate and charge or what. No, thank you.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: They got the order wrong. We got the normal chicken breast instead of drumstick. The breast meat was dry. BBQ pork was red and not charred enough  However the rice and chili were on the spot for us. Veg cooked perfectly. Can skip the dumplings. If you come in a group, order their other ala cart dishes. Taste good on ours and looks good on tables across
$1.50 for Nasi Lemak?  And pretty good too.. with nice sambal chilli... where to find???

Food Is not bad but the waiting time for the food are rather long after you scan through their barcode and order the food,  you have to wait around 30mins,  I have made prior seat reservations for 2 pax at 7pm and got in to order the food and food came around 740pm.

The mashed potato sauce also taste very normal,  nothing fantastic. The Vegetables were very dry and hard to chew too (tasteless)

What upsets me most is that they no longer have the fish n chips menu that I always ordered,  the current food that they are having on the menu also taste normal.. Not really fantastic like before.  I won't give a full 5 star for this place anymore.
The satays are nice. The fried items are surprisingly not oily. The lok lok sticks are great. The soup based are refreshing. And the service is awesome.
The service was superb.  The dajie always serve us with a great smile. Very friendly, make our every visit very happy

Nasi goreng kampung and nasi briyani are my favourites. Kinda sad they have to close early recently due to some issues, and not 24hrs anymore. We always patronise this place, its one of our comfort food. Good food and good service! Hope they will be back in 24hr operation :(
A neighbouring restaurant caters to family and individuals. Although the space is not big but it is aircon and price is reasonably ok as compare to others zi char restaurants

Super noisy.  Was there alone at about 3pm.  Theres this 2 chefs at the sashimi counter, a small build chinese malaysian and a vietnamese lady I suppose whom were busy chit-chatting all the way since I step in for my meal till I left, and still chatting!  Worst is I can even hear their conversation from the very far corner of the restaurant by the window.   Food is good I must say.  But ambience is a big minus!  Ordered a kimchi pot, a sashimi platter, a chirashi set and a soda.

Will go back again, but will peek first to see whether those 2 chaps are working together or not!  Lol.....

Buttered Abalone Mushrooms, Mala Fish and Mapo Tofu are a must try.
Nasi Lemak is also top notch!

Great food, great service!

Quite disappointing on the taste... Original supposed to be thicker in the broth than clear I supposed, however it was bland... The 'clear' version should be blah...  Ramen was softer than I expected...

I love the food here. Don't just think that coming here is just for the chicken rice. Their other zichar food like fried vegetables, fried tofu, sweet and sour pork is delicious.

My kids have been asking me when we can go and eat again.

Ordered their Chashu Chahan because I‚Äôm so obsessed with Japanese fried rice recently! üòÇ The Chahan portion is good, just nice for me! It was coated with lots of eggs, the flavour is quite mild and it‚Äôs not oily, which is good! üëç Chashu is soft and tasty. üòã

In a nutshell, mediocre food at premium prices. Steak was pricey and literally tough to swallow. Stuffed mushrooms tasted as if fabricated from the worn out carpet that covers the place. Apple pie ala mode was soggy and more reminiscent of apple pie soaked in commode. Save yourself some money and disappointment. Go somewhere else.

This "ulu" bistro was packed on a weekday lunch. Lovers of Malaysian-style chee cheong fun and curry noodles would like the menu here. Unfortunately, I find the food a bit disappointing. I ordered 3 types of ccf, 1 nasi lemak and 1 curry noodles. The tastes were generally bland. Maybe I am used to the more flavourful "San Cheng" Malaysian noodles which can be found in many shopping centres. The kaya puffs looked promising but the kaya and the pastry were not fragrant. They had draft beer and fried bar snacks here.
Not worth the long wait and ended with food that is not living up to expectation. First and last time. Ding Tai Feng or Soup Restaurant is a better alternative.
