Good food there especially the assam fishheadü•∞ the service there is not good even though the owner kept talking to us but the waitress didnt serve the tea or change the plate as norm. The price is ok but consider the service than it‚Äôs not worrhyüòâ
Small western food kitchen located in Jurong West. The portions are generous and food is delicious. Try the chicken chop with the different sauces. The platter is great value too.

Now bigger and better and with a wider range of authentic food from Malaysia. Price is also very reasonable for a food court and I must say it‚Äôs about the same price as eating at a coffee shop. Very popular so expect to wait a bit to secure a table for yourself and your dining partners. The bigger the group, the longer the wait. I always go for the char kway teow and steamed chicken. On weekdays, there a 50cents coffee or tea promotion. Best paired with the huge Amy Yip bun stuffed with chicken
A great small little Japanese don place tucked away at Tai Seng Centre! Food was really good and worth it üôåüèª

Good tze char food in the Jalan Kayu area, the milk tea is great and I recommend ordering it. Service is fast and prompt. My partner and I love the Szechuan-inspired food, particularly the kao yu. Tried the salted veg one and the signature one before and it was very delicious.

The only bad thing is that there are no options to put extra ingredients into the broth.

Had this a few times couple of years back and the food was so good. Ordered again and the standard really drop so much.

Prawn cake : mushy, tasteless, feel undercooked.
Tom yum : picture shown is already after scooping ALOT of the oil out.
Basil chicken :  isnt it supposed to be minced? This can in big chunks of chicken and the taste was totally off. Don't remember it was like this previously.

Only edible food was the fried garlic pork and green curry.

Will never order again from this shop.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Had a lovely evening at this Korean Chinese restaurant with my friends. Food was amazing. One of the best Ïß¨ÎΩï in Singapore. ÌÉïÏàòÏú° was savoury as well.

Do make a reservation as seats are limited

Although the price is on the higher end, the food is great and service is good.
Definitely more worth the price if you go for the set meal
Pretty low quality fish for average price. The cooked foods were okay but I was hoping to enjoy sushi. Sashimi portions were ridiculous and did not match the picture at all.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Pretty positive experience, staff were friendly and food quantity was fair and sufficient in my opinion. Pricing is reasonable too. Overall it is recommended, but not 5 stars because there was nothing special about it; other than it being a place for mookata. Also, take note that they only except cash.
Very worst behaviour of the cook... using bad words to the customer with family... never seen such a ridiculous behaviour of the cook today...

Had a family celebration for my dad's birthday at Putien because he craves for Chinese food. We all had a good meal with our favourite dishes ordered. Generally being a Fujian Cuisine, the dishes are fresh, light and taste flavourful üëçüèª.

- Fujian Lor Mee $10.90
- Steamed Prawn with Minced Garlic $24.90
- PUTIEN Sweet & Sour Pork with Lychees $14
- Deep-fried Eggplant Dressed with Pork Floss $11.90

Tried 3 of their Oyster Festival Dish, the bee hoon is shiok when soaked in the lor mee gravy, would be better if the oysters are bigger!

- Pan-Fried Oysters coated with Bee Hoon S$16.90
- PUTIEN Crispy Oysters S$17.90
- Oyster Pancakes $5.90

(Translated by Google) Sichuan cuisine with good cospa and delicious.

(Original)
„Ç≥„Çπ„Éë„ÇÇËâØ„Åè„Å®„Å¶„ÇÇÁæéÂë≥„Åó„ÅÑÂõõÂ∑ùÊñôÁêÜ„ÄÇ
Ordered self pick-up through Grabfood and the items were packed nicely. Noodles were ok and sufficient to fill me up. The price is quite reasonable for the quality.
Porridge prices are on the high side, expect about $9 per pax. However, the porridge is flavourful with lots of ingredients.

Long time nv eat.... since my sec sch days today my friend say feel like eating prawn noodles so i thought of them.. thought of eating this again....

Note order takeaway note they pack 1 plain soup is $2

Note they dont give u any soya with red chilli if want must ownself take / pack and ownself take also no carrier. U want u just take and throw inside ur noodle üòÇ. Maybe business too good. But im never returning here again. ( btw i run a noodle business too and i understand cost is increasing but $2 for plain soup and its not even the b1000 standard size its the smallest avail dessert container size üòÖ...and dont have a 0.013cents carrier for chili padi is ridiculous)

If u can accept all of the above then can consider takeaway.... if u eating there maybe need pay $1 for soup? Since takeaway is $2

A small restaurant with a very limited menu. Run by a very prideful chef . They dun serve chilli and vinegar will only be given occasionally. Recommended will be Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ Braised Sliced Pork Belly with Preserved Mustard Vege . Pork belly braised till  the fat and skin are gelatinous, soft, and melt easily in the mouth, the sauce is sweet and fairly sticky unfortunately this restaurant dun serve rice. The pork rib noodle was nice but a little blend. French bean was crispy and spicy. The popiah was something different from our local , filled with cabbage pork in a sticky savoury sauce. The chicken was heavily over dose with wine. The dessert on the other hand lack of wine taste. Their dish is more to the sweet note. Their dumpling skin was rather thick not my cup of tea .
Reasonable price & finger licking good. Friendly boss

So sad @5pm they ran out of their famous m.rebus power($5) so ordered soto ayam($5).T broth is more cloudy,heavy ,rich n a bit salty, it reminded me of a halal Ramen I had@ Ayam-ya restraunt in tokyo,I prefer a slightly lighter version,like t one serve @changi airport kopitiam. After a few spoon full I get jelak. I don't think will order t soto again, will only go there for their m.rebus power or maybe try their satay.
Ps. Rahim gives more chix as compare to t other famous m.rebus with chix n satay  sauce @ AMK ctrl hawker stall
Food is nice and price is reasonable. Love the prompt and friendly service too.

Decor is gorgeous if you like a lush moody feel, but the restaurant‚Äôs food and service are not worth returning for, unfortunately. We had the beef tenderloin (best dish), roasted duck (skin was good but I‚Äôve had better duck elsewhere), truffle rice (tasted more like risotto but nice), soft shell crab entree and seasonal veg (both no big deal). We were underwhelmed and didn‚Äôt order dessert. Food took a while to arrive, perhaps because the restaurant was crowded at 6pm. Service needs more attention as it was uneven. As someone else mentioned in their review, the design of the place also makes it difficult to catch the wait staff‚Äôs attention.
Best. I like this place. The Boss and the Staff are very nice. The food all are good. Thanks.

I have been eating this place for quite a few years and never had much problems with the staff. Price wise, agree its rather pricy. However, their meat is rather tender and juicy. Especially like the sio bak. You can request for oily rice. The chilly sauce for the chicken is really appetising

This place features a clay pot chicken rice dish which cooks over traditional fire. As each dish is cook to order, the waiting time ranges about 20-30 minutes. The rice will leave a layer of crispy burn rice at the bottom of the clay pot, this gives a special fragrance loved by asian family. The chicken is tender and fresh, adds a protein to the food. There is also some mixture of Chinese sausage and salted fish. Add on some dark soy sauce to boost the dish to a next level.

Visited twice in a week, skip the pork chop (also included in mix grill), too hard. Chicken cutlet ($7) and sirloin steak ($12) were good value for money. Fried chicken wings had nice crunch, worth a try at $1.50 per piece.

Food was delectable with reasonable prices. Have a good number of choices on the menu for families and friends!

A great homely atmosphere with friendly service staff for a pleasant evening out!
Looking for western food for dinner. Search using goggle and found this place. Food and service is quite good. Can try.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Affordable, great service. Now taking groups of 5. However, no reservations are allowed. You can have beer at the same coffeeshop while waiting.

The food is very fresh especially the fish and prawn is good.
We find the taste is just nice, not salty or the msg.
Is good to give them support and help them to pull through tis tough time.
Good steak at affordable prices in a quiet HDB neighbourhood. The pork jowl is so tender with hint of apple. Reservation recommended.
Delicious food, quick and friendly service, value for money.

$1 nasi lemak plus $0.50 either a fish or ikan billie; so far the cheapest in Singapore.  Other dishes like lontong, mee rebus, mee siam etc are sold from $2.50.  They‚Äôve nasi padang with a good spread of ingredients to choose from as well.  Delicious and will come back for more !

Definitely affordable.  I think portion is just right.. they have self order kisok at the entrance.. the only thing is instructions were not clear that there is drink collection and food collection counters. May be hard for first timers to self figure out.
Reasonable price and nice food.

Nothing special. Overpriced tho.

The sliced fish in chili oil was thickly coated in cornstarch. The knive cut noodles are decent but needed more salt.
Always great service and food. Family eating place.

Feels like I've crossed the border! üòÜ
Malaysian feel interior and lok lok skewers with selected soup base or satay sauce.
Choice of buffet at $28+ /adult or ala  carte with 80cents per stick for basic meats and veg,which are pathetically small in portion! Eg one slice of meat on one skewer, two pieces broccoli on one skewer.. There's also premium zhi char dishes which cost more, and BBQ marinated food for you to BBQ next to the lok lok.
Refreshing idea for a meal,but slightly pricey to have a full meal.
This stall has slacken in their food
The male waiter is pretty rude and the service is extremely slow. Food is so so and be ready to wait and be seen as transparent.
Foodies , should taste this outlet .. fresh salmon and delicios sushi varieties

Value for money lunch sets

Paid 12.80 nett for a 3 course meal with a choice of drink. There was no service charge nor gst which is awesome!

The food was generally fair. I very much like the chicken stragonoff with rice as it warms my soul. Service was fast and good.

Will recommend!

Tried their signature dishes, and found their Heng hua style vermicelli and "ru mian" to be delicious. The sweet and sour pork was great as well, but the beancurd skin wig vegetable was average.

Compared with the Putien chain of restaurant, the prices here are way cheaper and of comparable taste - in fact I like their ru mian better.
Food was great! Loved the Chirashi don
Very nice food and service. I have given one less star as one thing not to try is the tiramisu. Is like a pudding and have a very firm texture.

Satisfied - Happy and pleased with the delivery and quality of the food. I ordered a mini buffet service. Food was warm and well-packed when delivered. Drinks and cutlery were provided. The sauce for the fried fish was seperate to prevent the fish from getting soggy. Portion size was sufficient for 10 pax.

Dissapointed with the lack of followup service.
Called them on Friday night to enquire about the mini buffet service but did not receive any updates from them even though they say they will send me a WhatsApp message. Have to call them again later and the person told me to make an online order.

Meanwhile I would like to thank staff Xin Yun for assisting me with change of delivery timing when I called Gimtim on Saturday evening. üëç

Other than the lack of followup service, I would highly recommend others to use their online system to place order for mini buffet. It's well-worth the money.
Whoa. Tables not very far. It's OK. But dear staff, don't spray disinfectant on my food la. At least angle it away from my food la.

Worst western I have ever have. The chicken chop and fish fried rice is totally cannot make it. Totally tasteless is it Bec price went up so put lesser ingredients. Don't waste a dollar here there's other western around at toa payoh and also taste better and the price is lower.
Loved Their Sushis & Salmon Teriyaki!!

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Good quality dishes at ok prices. Xiao long bao is priced wayyy too expensive than other similar restaurants though it's delicious.

Love their crispy scallion prata dish. Yes it's just roti prata but they made it so crispy it's irresistible. ÁÇ∏ÈÖ±Èù¢ is also quite different from other places I've eaten at, but good.

Don't order the drunken chicken. It uses too much Chinese wine.

Tea and wet towels are chargeable.
This should be a destination and heritage dinning location.  Love the nostalgic ambience and authentic Hakka food. Must visit.

The service at the restaurant is bad and slow. My takeaway order of ONE dish took almost an hour. Needless to say, I saw many helpless diners waiting in vain for their food today in the restaurant. In particular, the cashier's service is very bad and rude. I recall that she used to be a staff at the previous Chicken-Up restaurant. I used the CDC voucher as I saw that they accept it. However, the cashier insisted that I had to 'round up' the charges rather than be able to use a combination of CDC/cash to make the exact change. A case of cheating the customer?
Simple Indian Muslim food that's good. An everyday place.

Unexpected gem :) The fish is super fresh and the mini don is good value for money compared to other chirashi places! Look at how much fish each mini don has! Also very instagrammable as each bowl is beautifully decorated with microgreens.

Had an issue with one of the dons (of no fault of the owner) and they were very kind to offer and exchange the don. Been a repeated customer and will definitely bring more people to visit this place! The cosy environment is also good for people who want to have a hearty chat over dinner.
Nice prata.. less traffic

Sashimi was on the pricier side and the texture and quality isn't worth the price. The sashimi was average and quite small for its price. Out of the 10 salmon sashimi, there was an even smaller piece than the rest. The swordfish was more expensive than the salmon but it wasn't good and the size was small.

Regretted that I didn't check the reviews by others before purchasing from this restaurant. You can get better quality of sashimi from other japanese restaurants or Donki.
Good dim sum at late hours. Authentic teochew settings and menu. Loved their fish porridge.

Very good service from Ani and very nice prata from Selvam. However, the female (chinese) cashier is the rudest person I‚Äôve ever met in my life. She was screaming at the customers in front for no apparent reason and refused to take my order correctly. Will not be patronising again unless someone else is the cashier.
Awesome and peaceful environment to have taste of Indian food. Customer handling and the way they treat you is nice. One of my favorite place in SG.

At the Nasi Lemak stall, I requested for no cucumbers. They gave it to me. I saw it and told them I didn‚Äôt want it, they didn‚Äôt take it out. I told them specifically no cucumbers 3 times. They asked me if I wanted chilli, I said yes. They didn‚Äôt give it to me. Not just 1 mistake, the attendant made 2 mistakes. Not worthy of a good review at all
Good food, fast service and convenient location.

Omelette was great but abit too oily, tom yum and green curry chicken had the freezer taste, lemongrass drink sometimes very sweet and other times ok mango salad was ok lor olive fried rice was rlly nice tho
Tried their food a few times. Their food have been consistently good and price is reasonable. Personal favourite is their crispy pork tonkatsu. Shop with good ambient, highly recommended!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Delicious. May have to wait a while before getting seats. Very popular. Cheap.

Got to try this restaurant for the very first time about 9 years ago when they were still located at Rivervally. Their fish porridge and braised duck are quite popular amongst the regulars.

Duck : ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è (can be softer)
Porridge : ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è
Salted Egg Toufu : Better to remove from menu
Pumpkin Yam Paste (Or Ni) : ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è (blend well before eating)

The Mentaiko Hotate had an extremely dodgy taste. By chance the Mentaiko fell off the scallop and I tasted the scallop on its own, it wasn‚Äôt fresh and had a questionable taste to it. ü§Æ

The sushi is pricey at $5 a piece.

The only saving grace is the Skewers.

Really did not feel that this was value for money.

The Hotate and Squid was an absolute rip off. I really wished I hadn‚Äôt come here.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Seafood restaurant with pond side seating area. We were there on a wet and rainy evening, and the place was nice and cool. Friendly serving staffs who take care of us through out our dinner - topping up tea, replacing plates, even check if ‚Ä¶

Food quality is really good but abit expensive compared to food  courts or other restaurants.
Also they need to improve their sitting place especially indoor.

Ordered truffle beef yakiniku Don with foie gras thru delivery service. The food is still warm, the beef is medium rare cooked and tender and flavorsome. There were salad and miso soup in the set too. Never expected such a high quality delivered food. I will definitely come and visit the shop soon.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: I was in awe when Hui Ping, your full time staff at the counter told to write the product codes for the food in bigger letters next time, otherwise she is going to key in the wrong items for us. Basically, i am here at the counter with the chit paper, to confirm my orders before making payment. Next, she asked me to read out the drinks product codes to her since she could not read our order. Telling her the code name and she asked, what is CF2?? Isn't this the product code your restaurant decided upon for the beverages that you serve? You must be joking with me right? You do not even know or bother to check what code goes to what drinks as someone who is already a full timer? The way you speak to me makes me feel you are commanding your customer. What marvelous customer service you have..

Hotpot ingredients were very delicious and fresh! The soup were also very nice, very well worth the price that you pay for the food items itself! Even better, there is a lunch time promo where there is a 40% off for the food items that you order, this place also has Shopback Go support which is even better after all the discounts!
Good service during weekday lunch. Food is nice and reasonable price. A nice place to bring kids too. Have student meal. The ice tea is nice.

Was initially here just for the dried ban mian. However, the chicken rice does seems to look appetising so gave it a try as well.
The chicken rice is average, but the ban mian is still pretty good and packed with flavour.
Did not try foods from other stalls as the portion seemed to be a little small.
Overall, the place is a little small so it is difficult to find seats but the ban mian is definitely worth a try.
Service ok. Food wise cant make it. Garlic bread not crispy. Seafood not fresh and tasteless. Chicken chop tasteless. Brocoli over cooked.

<MUST TRY>

Ordered their Chicken Chop. Their portion size is generous. The chicken chop is tender and juicy. You can taste the fragrance of the black pepper when chewing in your mouth. The coleslaw is mild in taste and has a slight sour tinge to it. It is refreshing to have and does not overpower the main dish unlike most processed versions.

I was lucky and had the chance to speak to the owners. I understand that most of the side dish are made in-house (including the coleslaw that I had). I think it is quite rare for an eatery to make the side dish themselves. The coleslaw is thinly cut by hand and selectively chosen to ensure that only suitable parts are included. Had a great experience and will definitely visit again!
Went for their Dim sum. Not bad. Taste good. Must try their custard bun (ÊµÅÊ≤ôÂåÖ)!

Value for money for what you get and taste. Today I queued for about 15 mins to buy the food and when it was about my turn, Makcik come and tell me and the rest of people behind me all sold out. Sigh!!!! Waste time queuing for nothing.
Food's pretty good... Too bad we didn't get to try the spaghetti we wanted due to ingredients unavailability
Tasty food. The salad was nicely done. The burritos was delicious too.

Wonderful restaurant. We had vegetarian food here and the taste is awesome!!!. Interesting point here is the service which is very good, humble and pleasant. Wonderful taste with wonderful service which is a rare combination,üôÇüòÑüôÇ
Food is good and price is reasonable. Except can be crowded during special days, when reservation is required. And they serve only set menu during such special days

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Located in SAFRA Toa Payoh.
Astons is the only other entity together with Superbowl bowling centre and Mcdonalds that have survived from day one it opened.
The premises is much bigger, compared to most other Astons restaurants and can seat at least 50.
Dishes here are of same standard as other Astons branches.
But somehow, they run out of FRIES on MONDAYS a lot of times.
Staff explained to me that their fries supply sell out over weekends and they are unable to get replenishment by Monday mornings.
Do take note of this and prepare to have other sides if you are coming on mondays!

Expensiveeeee!!!!! But I'm willing to as this nasi padang is a style of its own and more authentic then most so called nasi padang. My all time favourite as well..the fried chicken is awesome always..consistent as well. Alternatively there is other warung like pariaman, warung makan minang, sabar menanti..also there is one underated warung under hdb block cofeeshop nxt to the beach rd army market.

This place used to be Nana Curry. Not sure if the same management change their branding since nana curry had a lot of bad reviews the past few months or perhaps just a total change of management.

We ordered the salmon aburi don, unagi don, soft shell crab appetizer and chicken katsu don. All the dishes were delicious and well presented. Staff service was alright nothing fantastic but the waiter was responsive. There's many competitions around for japanese food but I wouldn't mind patronizing them again (fingers crossed their food standards don't drop as they are very new)

We didn't have issues with our food but the next table was giving feedback to the chef that the salmon was raw. Not sure if they ordered Aburi or actual raw salmon but the chef said it is suppose to be raw unless customers want it to be fully cooked. I agree somewhat but I think if customers want it cooked the chef can always offer to take the dish back and cook the salmon aburi style. Cooking sashimi cuts thoroughly is a waste but if the customer wants it more cooked why not compromise and do some changes to make them happy? Just gave me the impression that the chef wasn't willing to go the extra mile to help customers with their request.
We had a delicious lunch here. Recommend the salted egg mixed seafood
Very authentic Thai Food. For someone who eat Thai every other week, I rank it amongst one of the better ones in this area. Won‚Äôt be disappointed, noticed that the crowd are getting larger.
Food is generally consistent. Prata is nicely cooked with a mild crisp.
Good and affordable western food. Filling portion and a great assortment of sides to choose from

Restaurant is tucked in a corner on level 2, Purvis Street, one might miss the entrance if one were to walk too fast. I was there on a weekday night for dinner for my birthday celebration and was seated on level 3, which was private enough for a group of 5 pax. Ordered their newly created set dinner for 4-5pax. Service was impeccable, quality of food was served was of top quality. Food was delectable, to our delight.

In addition, the restaurant took note to serve the next dishes only when we have completed the previous one with a short time gap to ensure food prepared is warm, which many mediocre F&Bs are lacking in. Restaurant also allowed us to bring our own cake which is a plus point.

Special shout out to Zamzi, Iries, Nareenth who introduced and every dish serve, and patiently helped us to take photos and a gifted us a complimentary birthday shot of sake.

Overall it was a very pleasant and delightful dining experience. Highly recommended restaurant indeed, will be back!

Thank you Tanoke Team!

Had such a lovely experience dining at Tanoke! Chanced upon them last month during the Nespresso Singapore Restaurant week and made a reservation for my partner‚Äôs birthday for their 4-course dinner menu.

Everything served was fantastic, my partner and I enjoyed them all. Service was excellent as well. Would definitely be back again some day :)

$188 set dinner. The dishes that stood out for me is the imperial pot with fish maw. Full of flavour and ingredients, and the yam paste dessert with white nuts was good too. The duck was ok. They ran out of Garoupa, offered prawns instead. The crab seemed very small but tastes good. Wet wipes are chargeable. The day that we were there, there was only 1 staff serving. We had to help ourselves to the various sauces and serving spoons. The air-condition was not turned on until requested. Ala carte may be better? The dining experience seemed abit stressed being under staffed and humid.
food is above Average. but service seriously sucks.

Relatively new branch.
The food and service here better than Westgate. Enjoyed the salmon belly and unagi DMZ. The gyu don was authentic too, only missing onsen egg. Chicken teriyaki rice was also good! Husband enjoys the soba and he's usually quite picky with his food.

However, chicken namban was much smaller than sushi-go. Fish soup has alot of bones. Fried prawn and tempura are not as great. Coroquet was good.

Besides green tea, there's a variety of soft drinks and root beer! Generally good experience.
The standard has dropped, portion also getting smaller. The counter staff could have been friendlier. Miss the old soup spoon....
Good Western mix grill ,changeable options if you do not eat beef

Staffs attitude is very bad and rude! I think she need to send back for training and Management need to teach her how to behave and respect to the customer. One of the Chinese girl who work on Chicken rice stall on 8/8/2022 at 4.20pm.

Restaurant seems to not be able to handle the crowd after ease of dining measures. Called ahead for a reservation and booked for 4. We approached the staff to confirm attendance and ‚Äúenjoyably‚Äù waited for 46 mins (20 upon 20 mins and more), paying for carpark to enjoy the ‚Äúmajestic view‚Äù of staff serving tables for customers waiting after mine. They also kindly advised that we will only be able to get our seats after tables have enjoyed their dessert (an estimated additional 20 mins). Went before the easing of measures and food and service was still good. As for now, kindly reserve and enjoy at your own risk.
love the rendang chicken. gravy is thick and spiciness just nice.
Place is nice and there is pizza as well!

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Ordered fiery chicken with garden veggies(boiled) and fries.
Restaurant is barely half filled but orders took 30mins to arrive and everything is cold.  Not worth to even take a pic

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Got addicted to their yummy juicy grilled chicken. Their authentic Indian varieties have become my new favourite and my first choice. Highly Recommended üëçüëçüëç

Nice! Especially the fried oyster (Or Lua), the flour is mixed so well and thin it feels like it melted in the mouth, one of the main difference from the singaporean version. The "wok hei" of fried oyster and fried kway tiao is great as well!
Claypot chicken tastes great with lots of crispy "ÈîÖÂ∑¥" and comes with very compatible chilli sauce! Only slight dissapointment is the salted fish is too little in the claypot rice. I can hardly taste the salted fish, and the rice is lacking the fragrant smell of the salted fish.
zitimamas has great service as well as a quick fix for any cheese cravings that I happen to get through my week :-)
Chicken curry and beef rendang are tough, nasi lemak no flavor at all, i didnt finish and left, waste my $$$

Ambience: 5 Stars
Food: 5 Stars
Service: 5 Stars (Carol Cheng + Loong Yoke)

always wanted to try LAO BEIJING when they are in velocity, this is our first time trying and needless to say, it was an amazing experience and get our craving for peking duck fulfilled! üòä what i like about is that i can order half peking duck instead of other tunglok places that i can only order 1 full peking duck. - which allow me and my wife to enjoy not only peking duck but also other dishes üòä now awaiting for our dessert Tempura Durian to be serve üíï

Service was slow. Food took some time to arrive. I quite like the noodles but the meat was a bit tough. Xiao long bao was average and it didnt make much of an impression. Fried pork while crispy lack flavour. The pork belly buns are pricey at 2.50 each and I think the ones at paradise is better. The chilled chicken while tasty wasn't worth the $10 for a very small portion. The highlight was the fried buns, those were good.
Food is good, teh tarik not too sweet, prata is thin,  crispy and not too oily, staff is friendly. Price is v affordable. Will visit again.
The food does not live up to the reviews. Tried the chicken cutlet - taste and portion average. Not sure why people like the fried buns as it was oily. Not impressed.

Came here as I have been craving good claypot rice and read a review. Was quite disappointed though as the claypot rice was quite soggy and had no oomph to it. It was actually pretty tasteless. The meal was saved by the San Lao mee hoon and garlic chicken both of which were far better. That's a pity as the name of the shop is Sembawang Claypot Rice.

Ambience-wise, it's a non-AC coffeeshop space. There's no service charge or GST so don't expect service with a smile. Payment by cash only - no cards or Nets

It's crowded, seasonal items are often out of stock, long waiting time and sometimes the fries or the chicken are cold and soft. I'm not a big fan of fast food, but this KFC is surely not the best out there.
Food, tasty.  Service ... definitely not coming back.

The service is great, and the food is flavorful. It can get really crowded at times, but you can pre-order dishes for takeaway to beat the crowds if you are in a hurry, most of the staff here are bilingual, trilingual and even multilingual beyond that, so communication is easy for people of most backgrounds in Singapore
The duck was fresh and meaty and the food was decent. The staff here are very service oriented, helpful and friendly.

Had a nice lunch there on Wednesday. Ordered the steak lunch meal, fish lunch meal and seafood baked rice student meal. Steak was cooked correctly as ordered, fish was fresh. Baked rice portion was huge even for student meal and comes with plenty of prawns and calamari.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Such a terrific food I have ever tasted. I would rate -5 if available. Stay away!
Came all the way for the Ramen & Gyoza, nearby Bradell mrt. Awesome food, friendly staff & reasonable price.
Fluffiest prata that i have ever tasted.Liked the sambal though its abit cold. Overall a good experience very chilled n old school atmosphere.

Fast food quality. Instant Soup is cold. Beer is good. Speed cooking and speed eating training required. The seating is top notch like an aircraft cockpit. An one time affair. How to rate the food when we cook ourselves? ü§î

Brought my mum here for lunch few hours ago. The 2 gentleman that served us were very friendly and helpful. We had the 1 for 1 main meals promotion which was very worth it. Taste of the food was not bad actually so we are keen to return to try the rest of the food.

Something serious problem with Jurong point branch ‚Ä¶.. Today I been there at 5.30 . Ordered 2 plates of samosa ( 2 pcs each plate ) take away  and 1 samosa to eat in with one masala dosai . Requested give one samosa among with dosai but received after 15 min . Even request twice .
Later I comes to know samosa packed 1 each instead 2 each . Dosai received without orange chutney so I requested at counter but no one attend later again I ask one man he don‚Äôt attend .
Poor customer service and lack of customer attention.very disappointed

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Three words:Taste, freshness, quality. Service is attentive as well

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Teochew cuisine and service were fantastic. Thanks to Liu Lei who was serving us. The roasted suckling pig exceeded my expectations. Other dishes were good too.

Good Taste and Price.
Payment only Cash & NETS. Credit Card payment is Not Accepted.

Cozy place in a lay back area.  Enjoyed both the food and service.

Spoilt by the choices we have, therefore took us quite a while before we can decide.
Ordering your food with as set is definitely a better deal ($4.50 c/w soup, cake, coffee/tea/soft drink).

I like the Friday‚Äôs tomato soup with basil.
Lamb rack was nicely done, the brown sauce was not over powering so that with pinch of salt it brought out the goodness of it. $23

Ribeye steak was good enough for me, reminds me of Jack‚Äôs place. 220g (I think) of goodness at $22.80 as a set I feel is quite a good deal.

The MoMo was an experience. Mine mind was kinda confused as it looks like Xiao long Bao but of course taste different.

Will try the Oxtail stew on my next visit.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
Delivery:

Taste is good and very reasonable for the price with the serving size.

Tom yum soup is not bad but can tell got high msg and makes you thirsty - good for drinking in small doses.
Nothing special about their Nasi Lemak...Will not crave for it

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
My favorite place for Muslim food‚Ä¶ food are freshly prepared, spoil for choices on types of dishes, very appetizing seeing the display of their dishes , end up I want order some of everything.

The goreng ayam, mutton randang is a must!

Every I eat there- clear my place clean clean. Lol.

The price is on the high side for a meal.
Very delicious nasi lemak especially the sambal tumis. The side dishes are equally delicious too. üëçüèª to Sedap.
The service is excellent, food arrived quick & timely.  Love the signature chicken dish...it is to die for.  The only trouble, the price is a little steep.

Came for dinner on 15 Jan 2021 as the review was quite good especially for the xiaolongbao. We ordered xiaolongbao, seafood and chive dumpling and zha Jiang mian, it was so disappointing. The xlb and dumpling were TASTELESS. It's the first ‚Ä¶

01/01/2022 afternoon

finally, some good f√ó√óking food. delicious crispy prata not floury at all. kosong prata really hits home with its crispy exterior and soft buttery flavour. hot and delicious. teh terik and teh haliah poured hot and served, very yummy.

good customer service, friendly staff. free curry refill. fish curry is extremely savoury and piping hot.

standards have not changed and been consistent since 2019. show them some support! they only do deliveroo so eat there!

After confirming additional food order, the food did not come despite 3 attempts to remind the service personnel. When it comes to payment, it was promptly included though.

Updated review. Service has improved although they still miss out on 1 item on our order.
Great cozy atmosphere and nice Japanese food.

Quesadilla felt empty unlike other outlets. Ingredients were unevenly spread too. The others were okay. Speed was fast tho, received my food in less than 10mins even though there were other customer(s) before me.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: abit ex even if prices seem cheap usually mookata i spend about 12 but spent 20 here per pax and their drinks are wayy to overpriced
Retro theme local food cafe with good variety of curry dishes. Rice is a little dry. Tried coffee chendol but doesn‚Äôt blend as well as expected.

Worst place ever.
Tried the Fried Kway Teow, tasteless.
Told the black shirt guy (supposed to be the manager) that I wanted it extra spicy, he didn't even bother.
There were supposed to come together with a free drink which I didn't get too.
Other stall workers were great except the one that serve Fried Kway Teow.
The place is located at AMK. Lots of prata variety and the place is cheap! I would recommend someone that is prata lovers to come here and try out their food.

I had chicken chop today , was quite impressed with the taste , when I cut into it , it's so juicy and the marination was awesome . I could taste the flavour sips into the chicken,  oooh lalalala , it's so delicious!!

I love the coleslaw,  it has pineapple in it, my favouriteüòãüòã yummy.

I do not stay around  Ang Mo Kio but whenever I' m nearby , I will definitely go for their chicken chop .

Another recommendation is their spaghetti beef bolognese , don't miss it üëçüëç

Hope this review , will make you feel tempted to try their great foodüòãüëç.

It's worth to travel to Ang Mo Kio

Stay safe , Healty and Happy Always .

Always crowded near to, during or slightly after meal hours! Need to find a seat before going for an order. Tables are dirty as the cleaning staff are not doing their part to clear the plates and wipe the tables.
Enjoyed our meal with great-tasting dishes especially the duck. Prices are very reasonable and very good services and warm welcome by waitress. We would visit again for sure üëçüëçüëç
A small cafe which opens 24 hrs , standard food, price reasonable.

The stall presentation was interesting and fascinating. I was drawn into the stall and made an order here. Wanted to try their wagyu or curry but I know my son won't eat those instead I got ebi tempura. It wasn't the same as donburi at other stall. It came with sweet potato tempura as well. The egg was nicely shaped and looking nice.

Didn't manage to try the ebi cause my son took them all. I will come again to try their other dishes.
Mee rebus too much on the savory side.  I would expect a little sweeter.

Bought prata for takeaway. Reached home and was dismayed to see the amount of curry I was given (pictured). It was only a few table spoons worth.

I understand F&B is hit very badly by COVID but if this is how they choose to cut costs, I'm sorry but I will not be patronising again.
The menu here is quite special. Cooking is OK. Aircon helps keep you cool. If not enough, you can order a beer from Grain and Hops which runs the food court.
Food is yummy. Very good service. Even take temp and Sanitize all customers hands before going in.

From the qr code scanning to the food, it was hard to find a moment to appreciate. It took awhile to load the menu from the qr code alone, and even the simplest salmon sashimi which required no cooking was tasteless and not fresh. The fried items were slightly better but the entire menu wasn't worth the price. Everything could be enjoyed at a higher quality and lower price at Sushi Express.
Interesting Yunnan style eaterly. Nice presentation, and taste delicious.  Except serving for dessert a bit small. Anyway, the Cross-bridge rice noodles reminded me of my Yunnan trip many years ago.
Should've listened to these reviews food and service was worth than expected ü§Æ

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content:
Overpriced for what we were being served.

The Peking duck was cut in a corner and then served to us, already wrapped. It would be a better experience if patrons can wrap their own Peking duck. Some of us didn‚Äôt want the spring onions so we had to pick it out. The skin was soggy and oily by the time it was served too.

My soon hock fish was served undone. We had to send it back to the kitchen to re-steam the fish.

Overall food - so so. Don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll go back again.

We had the hot pot today and it was nice!  Husband got the chilli dip and I had the sesame dip.  Mix them both and it was really yummy!  Will be great if we can have different drink choices instead of the default lime juice :)
The food is good and the price is just OK. The place is clean and not fancy. Good waiters and quick.
Delicious Indian food. Wide range food you can choose.
Went to pack at Yakitori, Didn‚Äôt notice my tamagoyaki is missing a few cube from the stick until I reached home. Feeling sad right now.

Ever since I know this place, I never stopped going here. As I worked nearby (Al-Muttaqin Mosque), I am so lucky to be able to taste from breakfast till dinner. My favourite? Tandoori Chicken, Briyani Dum, Teh Tarik and the Dhall! I will always help to promote to mosque goers to drop by this place and also, everytime anyone mention about Briyani or North Indian Food, Al Zouq will be the first in my mind and I will urge them to try!

Although it serves mainly North Indian Cuisine such as Naan, Briyani, Tandoori. You can still have your prata or Thosai fix here! Should try the noodle here too!

At today 8.05pm , i was trying to order a char kuay teow from the stall and asking a plate without a beansprout as i not a fan of that. And the lady just told me that they couldn‚Äôt make it with a bad attitude  . I been here for a many times as they never say no before until today. Definitely will not recommend any of friends to here anymore . This will be the last i will be here .
The set meal comes with many different varieties of ingredients and the experience is just wonderful.
Nice but abit salty and oily. Price abit expensive too. Only 5 pcs with noodle costs $7 per bowl.
Fantastic! We loved the gam hiong fried mee tai bak, fried xo seafood rice, pork chop rice and fried chicken wings. Yummy!! Loved the wok hei and the sambal on the side.

Worst restaurant in Poiz. Not fresh and portion extremely small. Chopsticks and spoon dirty yet don‚Äôt provide tissue to clean. Only wet tissue and chargeable. See  this picture never see any restaurant put spoon and chop sticks without tissue. Sure the basket is dirty and never wash.

Fish balls soft, bouncy and tasty.
Noodle texture is perfectly cooked, not soggy or hard.
Pork lard is crunchy and fried shallots tasty fragrant.
Minced meat portion is small.
Overall good.
Avoid breakfast and lunch time crowd.
I tried their Nasi Sambal Goreng from Foodpanda and it was really good! Sambal was more on the spicy side but i can tahan spicy so !!! Will try their other food in future!

Mixed review for this one. ü§î
.
Taste wise, i think #AhPoonTraditionalBakZhang serves delicious #BakZhang (aka #RiceDumpling). The taste is great and savoury, and the ingredients are well cooked. I tried the one with #SaltedEggYolk and its yummy.
.
Unfortunately towards the end, i found a big piece of partially melted plastic in my rice dumpling. ü§¢ I mean, this kind of things happens, especially when it is handmade. Hence i discreetly bring it to the aunty and inform her of the foreign object in my food.
.
To my disappointment, neither did i get a replacement/refund (not expecting it btw), nor did i receive any apology. The seller is quick to justify why this kind of things happen. ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èü§¶üèª‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
.
#StanzFoodHunts #JurongPoint @jurongpoint #MalaysiaBoleh @malaysiaboleh_sg @malaysiabolehsg #ChineseCuisine #HawkerCuisine #ËÇâÁ≤Ω

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Food is nice and usual Aston's relatively high and consistent quality. However restaurant ambient is really dark and gloomy. Nice for dinner but not good for lunch....as it makes you wonder if its lunch or dinner due to the extremely dark environment with dim lightings.

Chicken Cutlet

üçú Food wise: Fries were hot and quite well salted. The cutlet was tender, well marinated and well fried. The lemon was interesting as it gives the cutlet a more refreshing taste.

This is surely one of the comfort food.

Side note, their steak smells really good!

‚ú® Ambience wise: Coffee shop ambience

ü§µüèª Service wise: Uncle was friendly!

üíµ Price wise: $7.50 for this plate of goodness.

Ordered two chicken chop sets, one with fries, the other with spaghetti, the one with spaghetti was supposed to come without sauce on the chicken chop. They managed to screw up BOTH ORDERS. Unfortunately only discovered the mistake after I arrived home.

Authentic and extremely delicious Thai food cooked by Thai chefs.

The Thai auntie taking orders is also extremely friendly and helpful.

Tried their Basil Leaf Chicken with Rice and Crispy Chicken Basil Leaf with Rice.

Will be back to try their green curry and pork dishes. Highly recommended!

Found this place by chance and the reviews on their Curry Chu Cheong Fan with pork skin. IN LOVEEEEEE. Asam laksa was alright and chicken chop was the saving grace of the nasi lemak. Had ice coffee but was quite tastless.. Nevertheless, will deft be back for the curry ccf!

The restaurant have wide selections of sushi and set menu. My opinion is that the food here are nice & good! Their price should consider reasonable.

If can, I would recommend to go early or during off-perk hours as there are always a queue and their waiting time can be between 20-30.minites. No reservation allow.

I really recommend this to everyone not to miss it! üëçüëçüëç

Super Old school One of the rate gems that has survived many decades
The gal ours almost taste home cooked
Service is personable
Price is  reasonable

Ordered the chicken cutlet fried rice with sambal. Very delicious and serving was generous. Fried rice was well done, not too oily while the chicken cutlet has just the right amount of crisp to it! Will definitely come again for more!
Always love the chicken wings. Home cook taste üëç
Food was acceptable, aircon environment welcomed in this hot weather. Pricing wise a little on the high side considering a Hawker centre is right beside with similar food choices.
Same group as the beauty in the pot.... ingredients similar with similar pricing... but have discount ranging from 30 to 40%. Service level not as good as beauty in the pot. Very different soup base.

Good hearty bowl of fish soup with bitter gourd. A hidden gem  unknown to many except for those working in the area. Sides were good too. Fish was a little stiff based on my visit but the crowd certainly didn't think so (very crowded during lunch)
Nothing much the price bit high.food is nice
Well priced for what you get. However, noodles were a tad mushy. Soup is decent!

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Decently priced, decent service. Came here in the afternoon so it was really hot. Liu sha bao and chee cheong fun were great; xiu mai and xlb were not so.
Parking is still challenging even with their valet parking service on weekend. Price value is good.  Food is of zhi char standard . Some hit and misses
Had the chow mien which was flavourful and tasty. Service staff was also prompt in taking orders and provided updates on the restaurant's relocation.

The staff (fat lady) at Jurong Point Branch is so rude. I think she feels proud as she works at Prata Wala maybe. Please don‚Äôt let these type of people to serve customer. Very terrible experience lol

$6 or $6.50 for chicken chop and fish & chip! Two big slices with generous side dish. Fish was still hot after 15minutes, and Pork Chop tender. (Menu no lamb)

Queue is long, but serving is fast too.
Hilarious to hear the lady boss keep barking orde to the cook (husband?) haha. Will definitely go again.

Haven't came in for a few years.
Quite taken aback overall drop in pretty much everything or I had a much rosier view back then when I was younger

Could tell they were understaffed right off the bat. Definitely got off from the wrong foot when they asked if I wanted wasabi and soy. I've never been asked that question ever anywhere else in my entire life in a Japanese restaurant when you order anything with raw fish

What would you expect the answer to be and what situation led to such a question in the first place ?

Doesn't help when it turned up with the blot of wasabi marinating itself in a saucer of sauce . This was  already pointed out by other reviewers and even with responses from the management, if there's no change its pretty clear things are not going to change . So please don't drop some message after this "you'll look into it "

Notice that tea ? It says refillable in the menu . But that's not the issue,  I choose that in spite of the fact i have utmost confidence it wouldn't be refilled because that's the standard you pretty much expect of the service staff nowadays

What I hadn't counted on is staff passing by checking the mug, peeping down at it throughout the meal 4 to 5 times  and not doing anything about it . I'm fine if your standard of service precludes refills but the repeated visits was as useful as asking me if I wanted wasabi .

One of the reviewers hit the nail on the head when this was described as something like a zhi char restaurant.  Everything feels like a tired  Chinese restaurant here
Food & Service was great! We'll be back again soon!

First time trying buddy hoagies in the restaurant and was pleasantly surprised (and satisfied) with the quality of food! We took away once during covid period and it was disappointing but so glad this visit changed our minds!
The fish was very fresh with a nice thin crispy batter, chicken was of a decent size despite it being part of the combo and the rib eye steak was perfect without the gamey taste. The baked potato was done perfectly, with the skin being easily separated from the potato -unlike most other places! Will be back to try other dishes.
Unfriendly cashier, super slow prata serving
Nice Malay food stall selling rice and noodles, both fried and soup form.
Loved the rice. Decently priced. Dishes fitting of the term "wok hei". Top up $2 for a drink and a side. Not bad.
Nice and delicious food

I find the interior of this place beautiful because it is decorated in gold and black with pleasant ambiance. Best place for small group gathering of friends or family. Food is very delicious, we love the roast duck and the sweet and sour eggplant the most. The portion is generous and guaranteed that you will enjoy every bit. Excellent service by friendly staff. This place deserves a five-star rating.

Food was great and portions were generous but the service was disappointing. Went there with my family a few weeks ago and was seated outdoors as there were no tables available inside. We requested to be moved inside once a table was available. We waited almost an hour for our food to be served and during that time we saw two groups of walk-in customers being given seats indoors. After mentioning this to the staff, they eventually moved us inside and a waitress rudely passed us their namecard and told us to make a reservation next time before coming. What a disappointing and awful dinner experience.
Good Indian food shop with a wide range of Indian cuisine

Always come here for their ËôæÈù¢Ôºå today decided to try their Lor Mee. I have to say it‚Äôs really good and flavorful. Especially the braised egg Âç§ËõãÔºåsuper flavorful. Really a must eat!

However sometimes the owners can attitude a bit.
Very good place for Hokkien food definitely intro their lychee ku ru Rou and also their Fried yam
Great place to taste authentic Malaysian food in Singapore. Conveniently located in Northpoint shopping mall next to Yishun train MRT station.

Grew up eating this and the standard is still the same as ever. The rice is always soft and fluffy. Chilli is on the sweeter side and must must must ask for more chilli to fully enjoy the whole meal.

Fish is easy to eat and not dry! Chicken is okay, great when its piping hot but when cold it becomes tough so do eat it immediately.

Always add Begedil! Love this, veryyyy yummy.

Have it there or dabao come also equally good.

Ordered a BBQ pocket meal, and a zinger box with a choice of chicken for take-away.

First thing, the BBW pocket was missing, just the fries and drinks. The zinger box was fine, it had everything.

Second, the chicken i asked for was original, but the one in the box was crispy.

Third, the chicken and zinger burger was dry.

The staff were not focused at all on what they were doing. I had to remind them for the drinks that came with the meal and the box.

Anyone who wants to go should probably triple check their orders, especially for drinks and every item they ordered.

Their only saving grace was the kind uncle that gives out encouragement notes to the students.
The dishes are very yummy. My kids like it and have free kids meal. The service is good as well. Jing Xue service very well and provide toys for my toddler and kid. Will come back again.
We had a very bad experience today with prata wala. Worst service. Too much waiting time. Food quality was average only. Please make sure the availability of food  before taking order.
Quick bite option. Usually not crowded.
Closed on Friday...no chance to try ..lol

Tasty yakiniku at affordable prices!
Ordered the 300g pork belly + chicken rice set, as well as 100g sukiyaki beef.

Love the garlic soy sauce with the meats!
Chicken tigh is chunky, and not marinated, hence not as flavourful.

The grill pan area was not cleaned throughout on this visit, hope this can be better!

Been a regular patron of Ichiban for many years with my family - possibly close to a decade. Mostly at JP branch.

Other than the occasional long queues during peak hours, there has not been much of a disappointment or bad experience so far.

The quality of food have never failed us and it isn‚Äôt too over-priced. There will always be suitable dishes for the young and old, and even vegetarian.

Wanted to commend a staff who left a very good impression on me. Visited the Jurong Point branch on 18 Sep for lunch with my family. The section service staff (Uncle) Charles was really warm and attentive. He would constantly be looking to serve the tables with prompt and smallest gestures and checking to maintain his service corner to be ready and neat. Impressed with his professionalism.

Went all the way from punggol thinking it's as good as 10 years ago. I'm wrong .
Ordering - sorry aunty if I spoil your day dreaming at 1.15pm on a beautiful Saturday. Wasn't paying attention on my order.. but got it done.
Serving- was fast with my egg and onion prata and one kosong prata with a bot of mineral water.
Food- as u can see in pic is a little black with some charred black ash on it. Crisp...Yes it's crispy.. but a little bland on the dough. The egg and onion too was crispy but also tasteless. A nearby hawker can make slightly better one which Cost one dollar lesser. Curry was fish curry. A little sour but it's edible .
Damage is less than $7.
The *best* part was having my meal halfwaynthru and I saw a cockroach strolling in the restaurant. Hmm.. must be the captain checking on patrons. I got a video of it as I do not wanna alarm it. Should be the owner who need to check out his "employed" captain.
I was giving it a two star but dedicated one to the captain :)
Fineline Band every friday!!
Very nice Nasi Lemak, better than other Chains. Always the comfort food when we come to United square

Located right behind the S11 outside of AMK Hub. The stall is fairly sized to accommodate for 7 tables of diners, orders are processed quickly too despite the vast amount of delivery order the store has.

Do note that the ramen does not comes with egg by default, it will be available as a $1 top up. Broth is not overly oily and noodles are al dante. Nothing spectacular over the ramen but it serves its purpose to satisfy your ramen cravings.

Bonus: Noodle upsize is available for free!

Prata: fresh, crispy, and affordable.

Leagues above the ayza restaurant nearby.

Honestly the nasi goreng kampung was the worst i tasted. Adding to that i asked for no veggies but mine came with loads of veggies. I hate wastage. The fried chicken and teh ice was good though. The food was quite pricey too. Overall decent.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Wonderfully flavoured Malay rice. Delicious and tasty. Popular place but the queue moves quite quickly. Reasonable price. Recommended üëç
Chicken cutlet $6, was tender and juicy. Well fried with a crispy crust. Sides were standard western fare.
Pretty delectable czechar in comfortable foodcourt. No crowd on weekends.

Variety selection of freshly prepared food items for rojak and gravy is good too..not very sweet and not too spicy! The only Indian shop in Northpoint that sells rojak, mee goreng, nasi goreng, mee kuah & etc and variety also drinks such as teh tarik and teh with ginger and other drinks too with reasonable price in shopping centre.
Came here for lunch and the food was great! It was very affordable. Will come back again

This place is inside ntuc. It sells malay nasi padang, mee rebus, nasi lemak, chicken rice, lotong, mee siam. Besides this stall is the cake shop. Of course u can do shopping in the ntuc supermarket.  Outside this place, there are many hdb shop houses and also a hawket centre selling varities of cooked food. Parking is at the multi storey carpark.
Tried the mala fish and taste good. Kids like the tofu too.

Impressive menu with authentic taste. Service crew is overwhelmed but kudos to floor manager Vincent who will make it enjoyable. Tom yum going is super fresh, soup emphases the fresh seafood on its broth. Fried fish comes with killer chilli sauce mixed with fresh veg

Top fab and fav: unanimously the prawns tang Hoon. Takes in the wok Hei flavour from the claypot . Prawns are of large size and till just right. Crunchy and not overcooked.

Had some good oysters paired with Prosecco. Overall great experience . Just a tad too loud and noisy. Probably all patrons too excited about the food fed to them

U Should give it a try. Moo Ping ( pork chop skewers are a must.

Tried the pork chop fried rice - generous portion of meat that outlasted the rice üòÇ pork chop was fatty and flavourful, and the fried rice was good too. Mashed potatoes and gravy was nice! Would prefer more options for accompanying sauce/gravy for the mains though. Prices are reasonable, even a little cheap for the amount and quality!

Waiting time (ordered at lunch) is a little long right now, but it's to be expected since it's just opened and the coffeeshop is popular for working crowd nearby.

Ordered garlic naan. The naan came burnt on the underneath and it was bitter with every bite. It even left a bitter after taste that their iced limau did nothing to ease. I‚Äôm not even sure if it was iced limau or iced water with two limes. And I don‚Äôt know why the iced limau came in two different sized cups with different amounts (two of us ordered the same thing)

Naan was really so disgusting

An after picture would better represent what we thought about the restaurant!

Authentic noodles, or at least I came for the noodles. Jajiangmien was really nice, sweet and fragrant, chewy noodles to complement, meat, bean and onions all mashed up in a beautiful dish. Japjae was sweet despite not being cooked with any meat. At least for me, this was a little treasure at a lesser known corner in Novena.

Value for money, delicious and large portion. The Steak was really good and the garlic butter was fantastic, definitely a must try! Chicken is really tender and juicy, buttered corn is really crunchy and nicely buttered with generous servings of curly fries. A must go to for those staying in the area!
Delicious

Went to AMK Jack‚Äôs Place during Christmas Eve night at 7pm. There was only two groups in front of us in the ‚Äúwalk-in queue‚Äù. There was a longer line at the ‚Äúreservation queue‚Äù and people had to wait despite having made their reservation. Waited for slightly more than 30 minutes before we got our table. There was only a fix Christmas menu for us to order from (but you can order the appetisers). The service was smooth and staff were friendly & pleasant. The food was of quality as well & didnt had to wait too long before our food was served. Overall, a good experience on a busy Christmas Eve.
Portions are huge, food tastes great, value for money!
Food is somewhat overpriced, wouldn‚Äôt recommend getting their frog dishes

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Ordered through Foodpanda. Did not pack the ginger that goes with the Xiao long pau. Even tip a idelivery rider to request for extra ginger. Not even get a single slice of ginger!!
great beef! Really good tasting coffeeshop hot plate steak. I'd come here over Jack's Place! Recommend the rib-eye!

True blue Hakka experience. It‚Äôs a really small restaurant so definitely recommend making a reservation the day before, especially if you‚Äôre a big party. The Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ and ÁõêÈ∏° are legit. Portions are generous and an absolute value for money treat. Highly recommend it!
Good

Tried the plain prata and egg with onion prata. Pretty crisp and good. But long queue on a Saturday, came around 0950 and we had to queue for 15-20 mins before getting a table. Once inside, the order came after 10 mins. Overall decent experience.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
This shop is always crowded and very little parking around here.
Finally, I stepped into this shop as early as 730am

Ordered a simple kopi Tarik 1.20 and a nasi lemak 2.80 which is at reasonable prices.

Didn't know is Michelin standard.  The wall paper said it all.

Lots of customers always.
The rendang looked really tempting to me.
Back again to this nice cosy restaurant inthe heart of AMK. The steaks are juicy and done perfectly. Duck breast is yummy. Pork tenderloin fillet is nocely done.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Traditional Hong Kong dim sum to satisfy all your circuit breaker craving! Definitely taste better than the looks. Easy ordering online for pick-up.

I mean I love Japanese food but I come to realise that I love the Japanese fusion even better. I think their seasonal set menu is really well designed and every dish is a hit in my opinion. The Hamachi Carpaccio is super refreshing and well balanced with tomato ricotta cheese come afterwards. Wagyu platter is a must order, I was super full when this dish came but it just tasted so great and I just couldn‚Äôt stop eating. On top of that, the service is excellent, thank you Iries and Nareenth !
Today's tempura Don was excellent. Perfectly done. However the miso soup was bland, couldn't taste the miso at all!. Dish cannot order take away, as it will be soggy.
Nice and friendly people. Need to have a better system on how to order and pay up. Keep it up and you will get there!!! Food is pretty good.

A replicate version of another popular yakiniku in Singapore. The service is great, prompt and friendly enough.

However comparing the price, this is slightly cheaper than its competitor. The main difference is the quality of the meat, seems subpar and lack of taste (more rubbery and bland) the other components such a salad and condiments is a no go.

For its price at affordable level but could be better, if you‚Äôre gonna queue 2-3 hours for this then don‚Äôt bother.

Borders close but you can consider dropping by this place for some Malaysia Lok Lok! I feel it‚Äôs quite authentic. They offer fried and steamed Lok Lok dishes. Thumbs up for their fried Lok Lok dishes, it was delicious.

Crowded but the staffs were still very attentive to every request of customers. Lots and lots of selection, the prawns were really huge, and it‚Äôs peeled! Favorite items included fried crab stick, sliced abalone, luncheon meat, enoki mushroom, cheese tofu and satay! Occasionally, the staffs will also go around serving fried items like seaweed chicken, satay, nuggets, chicken wings, fried tofu skin and etc.

Very satisfied after eating and 3 of us in total drank 9 cups of drinks!! For the buffet, it includes free flow of drinks, from hot beverages to canned drink, and even home made drinks like ice lemon tea and lime juice.

Note: Buffet is for 2 hours! Ice cream is also served at the end. üëçüèº

It was the worst dining experience ever. I had a complimentary meal there. Upon arrival, I had to seek out the asst Mgr at the reception counter to be seated. I was not even decently greeted by the AM. Not only did I have to wait for my table, I also had to summon the AMs attn that I was ready to order. I was abrubtly served n waited patiently for my steak which arrived 20mins later.  I had strip steak w standard sides. I was not given the rundown but had to ask. Midway, the AM sauntered to the table behind me to enquire about their steak. Not a peep to me on how I was doing w mine free meal. Having managed restaurants overseas as an area Mgr. I'm appalled at the lack of care and  professionalism at this Jack's Place. It seemed that the staff has adopted the scruff manegerial behavior!!!  Nevertheless, i sincerely ask that the owners of this place look into the operation. Fyi I visited restaurant at the tailend of lunch rush. I used to visit the very first restaurant at killineyw w my parents n service then was much more pleasant.

Had their $13.80nett dim sum buffet but alot of items were already unavailable or left one or two in stock upon arrival, what we ordered here are mostly what they left with on a Sunday mid afternoon.

Pan fried turnip cake, fried prawn dumplings, siew mai, ju chong fun are the better tasting items off whatever they are left.

My first visit here, not sure when they have most items but this place runs 24hrs, dim sum are all handmade, probably explains the lack of variety.
Not bad....

Food was not bad service of the person who brought us to out table was very good!

However the person who serve the dish just place our dish on the table loudly and have some kind of attitude. üòë dropped the spoon the the table when putting the dish and did not even help us to pick it up and not apologetic at all.

The fruit platter for birthday was nice however the cherry tomatoes were not good and tip of it turning black. üòî Disappointed.

The worst western food I ate so far. Nothing is nice.. Salad is sweet. Chicken is hard. Fries is bad. Rice got a weird taste. Black pepper sauce is with water n corn starch.  Hope you can do better, do something above average. I m really sorry to comment like this but I m not enjoying it at all.
good vibes and friendly staff! food here is really good as well, will recommend !!

Value for money.
Food is fresh and affordable
Suitable for small group or even 1 person
nice foods. i wish they have nasi lemak tho.
Generous portions from Fatty Bom Bom. Ordered the chicken cutlet and chicken chop. Find it a bit greesy but generally decent Western food.

Ordered Mala Xiang Guo. It didn‚Äôt seem like it‚Äôs stir fried, more of boiled in the chilli/spices and then drained the soup, doesn‚Äôt have the mala Xiang Guo fragrant. Price wise slightly expensive ($27.2 for 2 persons meal). Ingredients were really fresh tho, but found hair in the food. Will not patronise again.
Small cosy cafe/bar. If you are not familiar with the area, you might have a bit of difficulty finding it.

Ample carpark around, just need to find it.
At the corner of the row of shop houses.

First, the temperature scanning machine was the most advanced I had ever seen. Temperature taking and QR code all in one.

Wide variety of food. The menu showed a lot of food. However, the fish tail curry was sold out.
Service was alright. The food took a bit of time.
The curry fish head was fresh. Not bad. With lady fingers inside. Nice...
Also the plate of rice was very big. Could serve 2 pax.

The toilet was behind the kitchen. Need to walk outside to get to the toilet. Now let‚Äôs discussed about the toilet.
There was this saying, to know the cleanliness of the restaurant, you just need to take a look at the toilet. The toilet was amazing clean. Therefore I was quite certain the food would be hygienic.

Air conditioning was just nice taking into consideration of the hot weather.

Will definitely come again.
Long waiting time. Nasi lemak is very normal, nothing special. Price is reasonable, $4 for 2 chicken wings.

If you've grown up in Toa Payoh, you would have eaten or at least known this Nasi Padang. Hailed from 1968, they had been here since forever and moved around Toa Payoh Lorong 1 a few times. Saying I had grown up with this stall is no kidding, and I probably have their Nasi Padang at least once a week back then. Some friends have always said, Nasi Padang stalls love to overcharge Chinese customers, unlike what an out of touch MP said some years ago, $2.50 gets you Nasi Padang with Drumstick. Some would say because Chinese are rich, we charge you more. Others with a more logical approach, they are selling Halal food. While Chinese can feed on non Halal, we are depriving other Muslims of their food when they sold us their servings. In any case, I leave it to your judgement, I did had experiences when the same Malay guy ordered the exact same thing in front of me, and i did got charged at least $2 more compared to his plate of Nasi Padang at Che Rose. But I don't take it against them. There's only so many pieces of their delicious Fried Chicken and they do get sold out usually mid lunch peak. In any case, I am back here today at 1230pm, all I love are in stock (except drumsticks) and I am game to eat. The short queue in front of me are all Chinese diners. Figures. My order $11. All my favourites since I was a kid. Fried chicken, Beef Rendang, Bergedil, fried egg, mixed cabbage on rice topped with their curry chicken sauce and sambal. Some might think $11 for this is horrendous. I think its fair. I knew their Beef and Chicken are delivered daily. How I knew? Cos I used to know a relative whom delivered their beef fresh daily from Tekka Market. He had since retired but vendors he knew took over. Fresh supplies daily is not cheap in a coffeeshop stall quantity. That's quality food. And for the same quality if you eat the same in a restaurant, trust me you will be paying way more than $11. Tender and flavourful rendang, crispy and juicy fried chicken, freshness you can taste. Their Nasi Padang and sambal is of a very local Malay style. A familiar taste we grow up with. Now the pair of sisters took over from Auntie Rose. Still you can see Auntie Rose seating at the stall with a watchful eye. Quality and flavour totally the same from when I first had them 4 decades ago. I will definitely come back for more.

The food is not the best zi char out there but definitely very decent and has a home cooked feel. Not too oily or salty and we were very happy with every dish.

Curry fish head was good. They tried to promote their more expensive red grouper but we had sea bass instead which was already very fresh, moist and well cooked.

Only thing is because this place is absolutely so big, it is hard to get someone when you need something or want to order.

Nice. Taste is different from normal xin hua resturants.
Portions are quite big too.

There is -20% ala carte mon to fri till 5pm

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content:
New management by AL Mubin.

Prata is good and now it's served with two different types of curry; fish and vegetables curry. Chicken tikka ia tender and juicy too. Masala tea has strong taste, great to go with the prata and curry.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Enjoyed the lamb rendang, sotong masak hitam, and sayur lodeh with rice ($9). The lamb rendang was more spicy and sweet than typical.
Nice Steaks

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Ordered Nasi Lemak Cabe Ijo. Cost $6.20. Potion is good, very filling. Chicken is good and tender, not dry but juicy.. The green chili sauce is good also comparable to Â∞èËæ£ mala spicy level. Sambal chili is nice and sweet. Nasi Lemak taste fine good enough for me, egg was also nicely cooked. Only negative was the ikan billis that was overcooked. Other than that I will return to eat.
Previously order various prata for $6.40. Had the same order but was charge $8 instead. The person was rude and not keen in explaining the extra charges

The food  is exceptional! Very tasty and well prepared and you can chose among many menu options. I love the service at the place the staff Danes is so friendly with the guests and always takes care to offer the best quality! I highly recommend this place.

Have ordered takeaway Fish and Chip and Pork Chop from this stall many times this year. The portion is huge for the price. A set meal come with french fries, baked beans, coleslaw, garlic bread, lemon and sauces. I avoid ordering fried rice as it was cold and hard. On Sundays evening, they sell out fast. Must go before 7pm! Take note that the cashier auntie maybe a little rude sometimes.

Yummy dumpling and super affordable! Kailan also good but a lot of stalks‚úå. Overall, service was fast, staff friendly, however, should learn more basic englishüòä. Keep the foods tasty and affotdable.

Great Yam Cha for the weekend in Maxwell Road. The restaurant has a good  atmosphere and the service was great as well. The Dim Sum excellent along with the Yan Chow fried rice and Sambal Kankong . The dessert we had was the Mango Sago pudding and Herbal Grass Jelly didn't disappoint as well. Very nice üëåüëçüëè.  We enjoyed the experience.  Thanks Mouth Restaurant.
I like roti prata and ginger milk here. They have fried rice with chicken or anchve. Some have nasi lemak and teh tarik. Many choices for redidents and workers at May Flower station. Yum.
Located in Food Loft @ Blk 721 AMK Ave 8 (Beside Djitsun Mall). Nice Muslim-friendly (no pork no lard) donburi in AMK. Tried the flanked wagyu don ‚Äì not bad!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Came here for famous fish soup.

Good grills with affordable prices. Their staff were all very friendly and helpful which made the dining experience all the more better. The cheese pizza was not bad too, with its crispy crust. Only drawback was that the place was quite noisy during peak hours. Prepare to queue too.

Indian Muslim style eatery offering a wide variety of common dishes like dosai, prata, muthabak, etc. attentive service if a bit understaffed, but they hold a candle next to Springleaf just a few units away. A good place to drop by for Parthia if you don‚Äôt want to wait too long, Portions are larger than most places.

Be wary of the pricing though, as it‚Äôs not transparent - our single-person murtabak was ‚Äòupsized‚Äô without telling us.

Try the rava masala dosai.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Good place, taste is good but still needs to improve on service, I feel service is slow and not listening to what we were asking.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: I came alone waited for long, they never ask me in and only ask me to wait for table. Then comes a couple and immediately they told me no table already....so bad.

We had crispy chicken and rosemary lamb loin. Both good portion size, nice plating. Overall well executed western food and at reasonable prices!

Must try
Curry fish head was yummy and fresh but takes awhile to serve. Maybe can improve by cooking the vegetables longer too. üòã
Taste good.. the scent of coconut milk on the rice and the chili.. üëçüèºüëçüèº
If I could give this place 0 stars, I would. It‚Äôs been 1 hour, and the food have not arrived. Wonderful service, terrible preparation.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Very popular Nasi Pandang. Well priced and generous portions

I have been to Xi Yan more than 10 years ago at its own craig road branch and i never forget the experience. I like the way they make chinese cuisine fusion and yet did not lose the identify of the dish. So when i was deciding where to go to celebrate my family member birthday, i choose Xi Yan.

It was for a friday lunch and choices were between Xi Yan and other Hotels' chinese restaurants lunch menus. Xi Yan stood out immediately because it offers more variety and at a much affordable cost. Parking is also easy because Maxwell Chamber has its own car park. Car Park rebate comes with the dining.

The staff are very attentive and took very nice photos of us! Knowing how to take with right angle and background.

When i casually mentioned it was to celebrate birthday, they surprised us with the longevity bun!

It was still as good as 10 years ago and if not, it got better!
Come and try.. üëç

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: Carmen who works as a cashier for the TOA PAYOH outlet was very attentive to my requests. Her professionalism and exemplary service is a shining example for people in the F & B service sector. She was also smiling at the customers even though it was crowded. I hope that the company rewards such employees for their great service. I look forward to patronizing this outlet soon.

Curry noodles was nice. Chock full of ingredients. Special CCF is interesting though chye poh was all I could taste. Their CCF texture is probably the softest around even compared to HK style. But this is Ipoh style. So they don‚Äôt do char siew or prawn. And that is a real pity.
Good service, awesome food! The ingredients are fresh and the soup bases are delicious. My family's favourite...the teochew style soup...a must try. Lunch time promotion - 30% off. Good deal.

This is now our favourite restaurant !

Restaurant week menu is superb - from 2 appetisers to main course (Yellowtail cheek) to dessert + Nespresso .

Nareeth & Iries were very friendly . Nareeth was very patient in explaining the menu and highly recommended yellowtail cheek (Hamachi Kama) & he is right ! The fish was fresh and just simply delicious! We also paired with 4 types of sake and they matched the dishes so well.

We couldn‚Äôt wait to share the joy with the rest of family and have since made reservation for our family of 5 to visit again later this week. Looking forward to another delicious dinner with our family :)

Tims Restaurant & Cafe is a cafe me and my family will frequent as they have 50% pricing for senior citizens for selected menu. They are one of the rare cafe that focuses on Nepal food. Most of the choices are western food.
