Their western dishes are value for money. The portion is also generous. Set meals of $4.50 includes a drink (coffee, tea or milo), soup of the day and a dessert. It did not take too long for the food to be served upon order. For the coffee and dessert, you would need to let them know when to be served after you finish your main meal.

The ambience is also rather homely and is suitable for family with kids to dine in at.

#ILoveTimsRestaurantAndCafe

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Friendly and nice staff.
Staff is supportive and quickly serving
Recommended for friends.

A really cosy and beautiful place. Such wonderful and warm service from the lady who attended to us. The service is definitely top-notch, coming over to check on how we like our food, making recommendations and refilling our water glasses ever so often. Really made us feel super relaxed and comfortable.

The food was creatively plated. Especially the delicate cod with miso that I ordered, portions were quite small, but much detail went into the plating which I appreciated. Love the touch of charred lime which brings such refreshing lift to a dish that may usually be over salty. Love that! The lamb rack was also delicious and tender. Would love to try more dishes next time! A definite recommend!!

I called the hotline to try to get a booking but my call was turned down every time. Called multiple times over different timings throughout the day but same thing all the time. "Open for bookings" they say.
Cheapest nasi lemak $1 freshly packed - tasty. Add-ons like thigh, wings, beef etc tasty. Long Q in morn. Finish by 1pm or earlier.

An affordable healthier choice in campus. Tasty and light food, good and fast service.

Bring your own bowl if you want to take away (dabao)!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: BAD STANDARD OF FOOD AND BAD SERVICE! Ordered a medium portion fish mee sua, requested for soup as it dried up even before we stacked eating it. Was attended to by rude staff that additional soup will not be provided and arrogant chefs who just look over. Overall a very unpleasant experience. I felt that they have been complacent and disregard their service and attitudes and food standards. Used to be our family favourite however we will definitely consider other eateries. Not a worthy experience to dine here.

Ordered the following
1. Tofu homemade spicy XO sauce
2. Laksa
3. Truffle Fried rice
4. Kang Kong

All dishes were very cooked. There was an explosion of flavour when the Tofu entered my mouth. Laksa soup was smooth, light, super tasty.
Incredible satay sources for Gado-gado and I love the Mee Soto too

Ordered A Couple Of Times Thru Home Delivery, For Special Occasion.  I Must Say Food Always Delivered Promptly Within Selected Time Slot. My Family Love The Food Esp Lobster Porridge. Other Dishes Were Good Too.
Food is good

Enjoyed the zhi char stall especially their fishhead curry, salted egg chicken and claypot brinjal. The place is air-conditioned with high ceiling. For beer lovers, there's great selection there at reasonable price.
A new outlet just opened. After submitting the order online, first shushi came abt 30 min later.   Sushies were nice and fresh. Price was reasonable.

If i could give a no star i would...I was standing in front of the man who made the prata and i saw his sweat dropped in the prata he is doing..so gross their cleanliness are the worst I have ever seen.If u guys are there please take a look at their gravy with their kitchen towel was soak with curry and water dripping in the gravy..i couldnt explain more it was soo grossed.There are 5 to 6 people in the shop but their floor was full of rubbish here and there.(please dont give excuses bcos its busy).One guy he open up the rubbish he did not wash his hand he straight away take the prata and serve with his hand not using tongs.Omg seriusly eat at yr own risk..

Price for the potion was okay (smallest potion, could be small to others). Not much truffle taste but otherwise still taste okay! Need to cook carefully cos some of my meat either undercooked (at first) and then burnt at edges. Egg was kinda salty.
Good, staff are helpful, would recommend, tho needs more seats

Great value for money, strongly recommend a visit when you are in AMK. Run by Hainanese family.

Opens at 11:30, come abt 11:15 to beat the queue.

Ordered the Penang Laksa, Penang CKT and Penang Chendol x 2. Total damage $14. Price wise I think its ok. Taste wise I find it not bad. My mum thinks its very nice but we both find the cendol half-cooked (abit hard and powdery). Gula Melaka taste is just right but I prefer an even stronger taste. Otherwise would have given 5 stars.
Food was so good & delicious I would say. Price also very reasonable. Good service
super nice place, great thai milk tea and delicious broth!!! their potatoes and egg are the highlights for me :)

It's another weekend coming to an end. Decided to travel all the way to Jurong Point for lunch and ended up at Ichiban Boshi.

We ended up here because it was busy everywhere. Too many people in this mall.

Anyway, our lunch was just okay. I remembered that Ichiban had a much better quality but maybe that was years ago.

The menu definitely changed a little. I was hoping for a good lunch but got an okay okay lunch instead.

So what went wrong today? Firstly they served our soya sauce with wasabe in it. That's not Japanese at all. That's a Singaporean thing. Never do that!

Secondly, my SOBA was served room temperature. This should have been served chilled.

Thirdly, the Karei Karaage was not crispy as it should have been. This was rather disappointing but the flavors with pretty good.

The food didn't turn out so great but our waiter was amazing. He really took good care of us. He made sure our drinks were always full and he was very attentive.

Kudos to him!
Lady staff is very rude. Lady staff is behaving very rude when we ask a baby chair for my 6 month baby. Male staffs are nice and food also good.

The food there was totally not up to standard, very disappointed. The penang laksa no taste at all and not fish inside all are vegetables and noodles, the worst is the soup. Not recommended to there to eat. Thier porridge so expensive yet no ingredients, haiz.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Good food and nice ambience. Sipping a hot cup of masala tea watching the rain splatter away while a cool breeze sweeps over was blissful. It does help being located in a uncrowded and quite place, and it elevates experience.
The butter chicken and naan was great too.
Decent yummy Japanese food which is reasonably priced! Kids loves the oyakodon and chanwamushi !

Improved ambience, more casual family dining experience. Great service crew, and received attention from presumably the establishment owner, who was keen to have our views on the test debut of the lamb shank, which we encouraged him to have it as a regular item on the menu. I had the briyani with the said lamb shank and it was both visually appealing and palate pleasing. I also managed to wolf down a couple of pratas as well. Am returning for a repeat meal in a couple of weeks' time

Visited JJak for the first time yesterday with my god-daughter and we both love the small but cosy ambience. The food serving is generous and when we sink our teeth into our Mentai and teriyaki salmon, we were immediately drawn to the freshness of the food. The Thai milk tea was excellent as well. We highly recommend JJak to anyone who love good food and we‚Äôll definitely be back for more! üòãüòãüòã
Their hor fun was awesome. Both me & wifey love it very much. Service was extremely fast & well packed.

We were here for the vet's appt and was so glad for a cafe that welcomes little friends. Better than that the food is very good. The pasta was fresh yet light. We also had the croffles with a very crispy chicken. I would have stayed longer for dessert but with the current humidity we have to come back when we can sit indoors without the little friend. Very good dining experience and good offering of wines too!
Good place to hang out with friends, especially at night as it is open 24 hours. The good is good and the price is also reasonable. Very good prata can be found here.
Their fish n chips yery value for money and taste great! The sides are curly fries.  I luv the lychee tea too‚ù§Ô∏è A bit secluded spot
Wow the current promotion very worth , my son brought the beef platter from roman tei very nice

Food portion is small and cold. Waiting time for food is damn long. Food taste is horrible. Not worth to try. Overall, worst experience.  Even a plain roti prata taste better than all the dish served!!!

It is always our pleasure to dine at the Malayan Council.  It is our 1st time at the Winstedt outlet and were pleased with the outstanding service and food served.  A special shout out for Ms "Misha Omar" for her spontaneity.  Really had a great time dining at the restaurant.  We will surely be back!
Thanks for the good food!

Authentic Anson fare. Love their Curry Pig Skin and Anson Special. More mint leaves might help enhance the flavours for their Penang Laksa. Overall a wonderful dining experience with very authentic Malaysian fare.  üòäüëçüèª

Small little restaurant with only 7 tables
Hidden at a corner of a HDB block.
Reservation is a must
Food is home cook style nothing special
Some of the fryed dishes are abit oily
Come in small portion
Prices are slightly high
Worth to try are the pumpkin ball, xiao long bao, shen jian bao and popiah
Cash terms only
Aunty serving got alittle attitude problem
Plenty of parking lots right behind the block.
Nice and quiet, sushi is delicate and much detailed!

I have been having my teochew fix here for awhile now. Love the fish steamboat! The soup is milky and rich and full of ingredients. Theres fried fish in it and also a plate of raw fish slices, tons of veg and fried egg in it. Love the braised duck and my dad loves the pork jelly. Theres another branch at bukit batok which I frequent as well but tt outlet doesnt have steamboat option. Overall great place and portion is very generous too! üòç
Bloody 30mins for one apple pie, the brigade is inefficient inside the kitchen, the manager has no assertiveness over the members

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Good soup base as clear tomyam

Auntie handling the order is very rude and has very bad attitude , speak like we owe her money. Got my order wrong and still insist I order wrongly. The pork chop is abit dry but the sirloin steak is bad. Stopped eating and ordered other food instead. Order at your own risk

Perhaps I am not over-exaggerated to say that this place, by far, serves the best Thai food in Singapore! Authentic home-cooked Thai food prepared by awesome chefs and the staffs are never lack of smiles (now you know why they call Thailand the "Land of Smiles").

Always friendly and courteous to compliment their great food. Price is very reasonable for such quality. Must try includes the tom yam soup and spicy basil chicken.

Has been to many Thai eateries throughout the island, but none came near D.K. In fact, the standard here may be better than what you would find in Bangkok!

If you're looking for some comforting Thai food, you know where to go.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: June 2022: came for dinner to satisfy dim sum craving for dinner. Had a few long only cos we were not that hungry. It‚Äôs part of a coffeeshop and not fancy at all. Food was ok, not as tasty as those hotel level dim sum, but better than the typical coffee shop dim sum stalls. Stall owner had great service too. Even selected a few videos for us to view while we were having dinner. Maybe cause we were seated at table 2 - right in front of the big screen. We thought all the dishes were actually tasty. I liked the Paper wrapped chicken the best! Good choice for dim sum dinner near home.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: An affordable hawker center with a wide selection of food, but my personal favourites are the porridge and hokkien mee stall. You can have a meal here for $5 but it can get quite crowded during lunch time. Also be careful of hungry birds!

Very good food and
people
Patiently  answered  my queries and doubt
On my order .

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Its not what I expect to have here , its a wonderful moment my stomach could have with fresh Wagyu and delicious choice of seafood . If youre grill and steamboat lover , this is the place you want to try . Oh ya , thanks me later , lot of offer&promo going on . Watch em out .

My all time favorite chilli pan main. Not too spicy and oily. Everything just right and with the half bolied egg it exploded in your mouth. Must eat every time I'm here. Together I will always order the fish ball noodle. You could taste the difference from our Singapore style. The whole meal experience made it felt like you're in Malaysia. Missed going MY.

Went with my family and friends and we had a great dining experience at Tasha‚Äôs! The staff were very patient and helpful. The Mee goreng Ayam, Nasi goreng Ikan Bilis, Nasi Goreng egg, Chicken Murtabak we ordered were exceptionally delicious! Will definitely come back to try more soon! Thanks for the great food!

Good for casual dinner with family .
The drunken chicken was not chilled enough and chicken were chilled into too small bits .

The noodle was ok but nothing unusual .

Fried pork on skewers was too overly sweet .
The skin of the  pan fried bun was too hard.

One major comment was after consuming dinner I was overly thirsty, too much artificial flavoring.
Love having their sushis with my family. Great prices and great quality of sushis.
The foods are good. Been here plenty of times, and they managed to maintain the quality. But be prepared for long waiting (queue) time, especially on weekends.
Great place, nice food!! Will definitely come back again!!
Nice prata. Have been their customer for many years already.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Good korean food near maxwell food center. Lots of koreans patronising this restaurant as well. Spent around $90++ for 5 people, price is decent for alacarte mains. They also provide the standard radish and kimchi side dishes. Overall good experience.
Toasted eggplant sandwich is very goodÔºÅ

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Prices has gone up abit, but I guess that's happening everywhere. The chicken rice set (be it dumpling soup or vege set) are now $10.50 but a drink (barley or lemon tea) is added to it. Food standards still good.

Visited 11/7/2020
The zha Jiang mian is fragrant and has hint of peanut. The Chinese pancake must try, pipping hot paired with their in house chilli paste makes it very awesome. ‚Ä¶
Enjoyed the concept of solo BBQ! It can really be done within an hour! The portion is just right for me. Choice of sauces were good. Didn‚Äôt have a long wait on PH lunch time~ will go back again

One of the BEST Thai Food in SG. Good and reasonable price premium set meal. Their ala cart menu is also good too. They serve Fried Papaya Salad - pretty special. The Seafood Chilli sauce is also very nice. Their staff is friendly especially Ice is very friendly and open for conversation. We will definitely return to try more of their Thai delicacies.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Not bad. Will come again.

We don‚Äôt have too many people so we could only sample some of their Hakka dishes but so far all have been fantastic. The boss even threw in a small appetizer Hakka spring roll which I guess was to thank us for our patience in waiting for a table. Services were good! Felt quite homely and like the older days when you still can see the boss in the restaurant, which is unlike most other that have been commercialized. Price was reasonable.
Our favourite "Western food" place right now.   Well priced menu and appropriate expectations.   Big fan of the Pineapple or Hawaiian Chicken Chop carbonised like Han Solo, but in cheese.

First and last time that I'm paying money for such food, terrible attitude and service.

Ordered through Grab for self-pick up. Noticed a couple of my items missing but there was no staff to clarify.

Very hard to get the attention of any of the staff. Finally managed to get the attention of the staff manning the claypots, he rudely told me that all the food was packed and I should check.

I had to raise my voice and tell him that my items were missing. He yelled for another staff before he found my missing items.

If this was a grab delivery, my order will definitely have missing items.

Foodwise, curry chicken noodles had a lot of oil. Counted at least 10 tablespoons. (Gave up after a while)
Chicken rice, char siew rice, ban mian, claypot rice all so-so. Nothing stood out
Food is reasonably priced and tasty

Never been to this part of Toa Payoh, was surprised to find this authentic Thai Food restaurant here.
Had dinner here with my family, service was good, service staff very friendly and food was delicious.
Bon Appetit!
goodÔºånot expensive, beer Qingdao $6 one bottle,
Nice food of Malaysia although not all stall is open but most of them still selling. Food is better than Malaysia chiak.
Food is okay but not great, not worth to travel the extra mile for. Curry mee is overrated.
It was a great lunch at umisushi specially the rice dumplings.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Chicken rice - The dish was good but the chicken meat was not as fleshy as before and the portion was smaller.
Dumpling soup - There were 3 dumplings, which were ok. But the soup was salty and did not have much other flavour.

The high tea buffet is super value for money. You get delicious food with freshly made dim sum. The menu is periodically updated so you get new food items once in a while. Fried food is piping hot and on point, seasonings all well done. As it's a buffet, we also love that the quantities are perfect for tasting, just order a few more if you want! We're repeat customers and we'd continue coming!
Chilli crab sauce Lala, Thai sweet chilli sauce crispy tofu, stir fried beef are must orders.

Food was decent. Ordered the Salted Egg Chicken with Fries Rice set lunch. The chicken was yummy, the fried rice was a little bland, and they gave a lot of rice (like 2 persons portion). Had to wait a long time for the soup (soup of the day) and my food to come. Quite surprised by the wait cause usually set lunches allow restaurants to narrow down the food preparation and serve quickly.
Food is good, service is great and price is reasonable üëå

bought 3 rice dumplings, both fillings only a bit, full of uncooked rice. staff is rude, and don't know how to tie different colour string for different dumplings.

at first i thought it's only 1 piece maybe they put a bit of meat only, turns out all 3 pieces inside meat like this photo.

see photo yourself, $3.80 each, a few meagre pieces of dry hard meat. taste bad also, don't think will even try the restaurant. please warn others.

honestly, i have never been so angry, and tasted something so bad. i have had better one that only cost $2.50 each with more meat inside.

pokgai pui cao nua
Look at the chunks of white rice. You call this fried rice? Speechless. üëéüèºüëéüèºüëéüèº

Frankly not the best sushi operator, but unlike other reviewers, I did enjoy my sushi dinner in Sushi-Go. Ordered the food and most of our orders came within 15 mins? That‚Äôs fast. Hot food served hot, fresh food served fresh. But just thought the Japanese rice was alittle too thick in taste. Requested the staffs to help us top up the green tea powder a few times, they were quite prompt too. Price and quality üëçüèº.

Thought it would be great to have more food choices, for e.g. Fried food; like fries perhaps?
More chawanmushi selections?

Overall, Place was clean, pleasant to have dinner. With every $20 spend, you get a play at the claw machine.. oh ya, u only have 20 seconds at the claw machine ya.
Wouldn‚Äôt mind with attitude, yet 7 SGD for only TINY portion of meat in Bak Kut Teh, and there‚Äôs barely meat but fat.
For late night meals - egg prata and teh C.   üëç

Table reservation was made before HA, and Edwin was kind enough to notify and offer takeaway for the main event, which was the A5 Wagyu for 4 pax.

Pricing and order was clear and speedy, with care taken to ensure quality of food served. We ordered 1/2 rack of ribs and 720g A5, along with side dishes.

Packaging was done to ensure the best possible quality when served, and Edwin even offered to load the food to my car.

Impeecable service and taste! Will definitely visit again, be it for dine-in or takeaway.

Let's support our local businesses, those who take extreme pride in the service they provide!

Ordered from Foodpanda.

The curry fish head is soo goooddd‚Ä¶.the thick, flavorful, creamy, spicy curry compliments the sweet and juicy fish so well. Comes with some eggplant, taupok, and some vegs.

Their veg and omelette is nice too.

Don‚Äôt be mislead by the ugly photo I took. It‚Äôs 100% worth the try ü§©

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Stand there wanting to order and yet the female staff just stand there use her phone and do her own stuffs despite seeing me. Another uncle came and she just took his order.. what kind of service is it. Waited 5 mins and staff just can't be bothered.
The fish is one of the freshest I've eaten. Pricing is reasonable. Eating fish steamboat or cray pot curry fish head in aircon area, best!

This place is small and cramped. Expect some waiting time if you're planning to dine in here. This more like take-away food cart.

The first step into the restaurant nobody was assisting us to be seated. One of the male staff can be seen just standing and looking around, barely moving. Next we placed our order and it was fast serving for the main items, but the drinks and some small side orders not to be seen. We had to ask twice for it to be served.

The food was OK OK only, not so amazing, but the pricing was more towards the expensive side compared to any other Indian restaurants.

Takeaway the famous pork chop AND LOOK at the value for money omgosh it was 2 big pieces of pork chop and sides for $6.50. cheaper than Aston's !! It was still nice even though dabao a bit cooled down
Very poor operated shop with unfriendly service. ONLY NEAREST prata shop to eat.given a choice will not patronise them.

This place is located at the heart of NTU in Northspine! (Near the KFC). I was decently surprised by the ambience! It was cosy and comforting.

I ordered the beef cheeks, pork loin fajita, wagyu burger and lava cake.

The Wagyu burger was disappointing. It cost a whopping 18 dollars! However, the patty was really bland. There was no seasoning at all. I had to add my own pepper and salt to the patty to make it tasty. The onions were raw and not grilled. However, I have to say that the fries were good! ($18)

Next, the beef cheeks were soft and tender to the bone. Sauce was decent and mash potato is creamy! However, there's not enough sauce to pair with the mash potato as it was paired with the beef cheeks. (Preferred the fries). They could have been more generous with the salad portion. Overall a bit too pricey for this dish. ($22)

Lastly, the pork loin fajita was surprisingly good!! Pork was cooked and seasoned well! It was paired with onions which was good as well! The combination with the wrap and the pork was really delicious. It even came with a side of sour cream and guacamole! Overall a really really good dish that I recommend :)) It was the cheapest out of the 3 main dish. ($16)

When dessert came, I was pleasantly surprised on the presentation of the dish. The lava cake came off a bit sweet but paired really well with the vanilla ice cream. (Although they probably used a cheap ice cream brand) A great way to end the meal :) ($6)

Overall, dish place is a must try if you have the money as it comes off a little pricey. Would recommend if you are finding a place to splurge. Till we meet again, au revoir!

This outlet is more spacious than some. Here you can enjoy the signature curry dishes comfortably in the nostalgic decor to resemble Singapore in 1960s. The portion of the curry chicken is pretty huge and delicious. The curry is the thick kind, goes well with bread too. Other dishes I have tried are the curry chap chye, nasi lemak with crispy fried chicken wing and ngo hiang. Stick to the curries, they are good.

I've been to the restaurant numerous times and the food has consistently been top-notch and absolutely delicious!! I really love that they are innovative and when you ask for recommendations, the staff is always fantastic with recommending me very tasty dishes üòãüòãüòãüòã It's the perfect place for a family dinner or gathering with friends. Thanks for the lovely experience, will definitely be back again!

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content:
Food was great and staff was very friendly!
( Dava, lotus, Karthi, chief and big bro )
We order paratta naan... which was super fresh and crispy.I would come again, highly recommend....üòä

If there is a choice I will put ZERO STAR. I am Utterly disappointed with the food. Its so bad that this is my first time reviewing about food.

Upon collecting my way Signature Wagyu Flank Donburi. To my surprise I saw the beef looks like well done. The person in charge mentioned that the beef is like that don't bother seeing the picture as it's illustrated and he quoted 'this is OUR standard'!!!!!

The beef was dry and tough, the rice was too dry and it cost $17. Its my WORST experience.. its so bad that I have no words to for it. I went to ask around and many had experience it too. SO Please don't go through this terrible experience!! And learned from our mistake..

Ps. Do not be fool by their Head and Master chef marketing!!

First time visiting this restaurant. Walked in and was told all tables fully booked, even when we were prepared to wait. So did an online booking and visited the restaurant the next day.

Ordered Ribeye and Home Cured Bacon Thick. Ribeye was juicy and nicely grilled. The Bacon Thick was excellent. Prices are very reasonable, no service charges nor GST. Will be back to try their other items.
Nice place to grab and to eat wide variety of Indian Muslim food.

Wonderful modern Chinese cuisine - very private place. Beautifully decorated. Service is very good. The portions are relatively big - so it can be a good sharing set with a group of friends. I personally like their duck cuisines; very tasty.
So yummy... Toufu is very crispy , must try it ... all food was delicious also ... love the all...
Tired the fried carrot cake in dark sauce.. all I  can taste is only the dark sauce sweet taste..

Air-conditioning, the food is good and well deserved, waiting time just also good. U might want to try masalah with briyani. Taste good for me. The price not so cheap but not so expensive either. However, the parking lot a bit far to reach this shop otherwise u come by public transport.
Experience here was overall really good. Waiters were really friendly and the mala xiang guo was so damn good including other side dishes like mapo tofu. Prices were also reasonable
Over price for students.. and food is lousy
Fun food for a late night snack with friends, I recommend the broccoli, seaweed chicken and breaded scallops. Service comes with a smile too!
Love the curry chicken cutlet udon! Reasonable price!
Food is ok but I have ordered Grab delivery from them twice and they forgot the soup both times. Unbelievable.

A frequent patron here.
One of the best places to have western food apart from Ashton's.

Pictures speak a thousand words.
:) Do note the crowd during peak hours.

Tamako Meal has always been in our must visit list of Japanese Restaurants in Singapore. Their meals are simple yet authentic, never compromise in food quality and always ensure us with sufficient portion. Never miss their Giant Squid and Tuna bowl for our every visits. Owner is always friendly and chats with diners occasionally. Awesome place. üëç

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: came across Signature Restaurant while surfing, thought of trying from new place. Both North Indian & Indo Chinese, food delivered before given time & turned out very tasty & in very good qty too. Thanks to  the restaurant & chef

This place is absolute trash. Waste of money for what they provide. 3 tiny slices of toast for a dish meant for 2? I'm supposed to split the 3rd one down the middle? $28 for an anemic excuse of a steak?
Sausage platter is straight off the frozen meats section at NUTC. Quick pop in the air fryer and on to your table. Bland and boring.
Amazingly, its crowded, proving once again that us Singaporeans will support absolutely any terrible place, so long as it's accessible. I mean, that's why I came down.

Save your money and go to a better place.

Food served cold during weekday lunch . Waited for long time to be served lunch.
Service was bad with staff more interested in their phone than customers.
Service was bad.
Food quality deteriorated .

‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

I am impressed by ThaiLily Restaurant and will visit them more often.

Yesterday they forgot to pack my honey ribs. I message them in FB and they were responsive and responsible.

Just now, I went down and order dinner at Thai Lily again. Told the staff about the missing honey ribs. He okayed and I went for a smoke. Came back to restaurant and he packed an extra mango sticky rice. Said complimentary from his boss. So nice of them.

In term of food quality, they are above-average Thai food. The sea bass dishes are attractively priced at $12.90 and come in 5 styles, and my family love them.

They are located at Block 107 Lorong 1 Toa Payoh #01-268. Beside Phoon Huat/Redman Braddell MRT.

Ordered their basil pork, tasty and good portion. Good tomyum soup with quality ingredients in it. Overall worth going back and recommendable!

Only downside is long waiting time - Waited for almost 40mins for my takeaway during lunch.

Had a chance to have lunch at Ichiban today... Had ordered the Saba and rice as a simple dish for myself.

When the fish came, i taste it and feels cold and the fish is like not grill and doesn't taste fresh...
Spoken to the floor manager, Mau whom was a nice lady whom came and make a replacement on the Saba.

2nd pieces of Saba came but to no changes... warm but could feel the meat is so hard which shouldn't be (see pic). Mau came to ask for review of the fish but she knew it wasn't good.. she initiated to change to Salmon. Meanwhile, she apologised and gave us a plate complimentary sushi..

Finally, the salmon came and the meal was completed.

I have to compliment the assistant manager named, Mau. She was very good and professional in serving customer and cater to their needs. Thanks Mau for making my experience worth while during the short period.

Personally I prefer this Indian stall to others around the area. The standard of food is there and the variety of choices available is also there. Their western is a super worth while option because for a whole chicken cutlet combo with coke cost $6.50 or so(for those seeking protein til 11pm) friendly customer service and jovial owner. Easily accessible by private transportation but may need to walk a bit if taking public transportation. Really close by the wet market for shopping

We came in for a late dinner on Monday 17 Jul 22. Despite not making any reservations, the team still accepted our group of 3.
We were served by AYU who was very pleasant and accommodating.
Hats off to the team for their amazing service!
The food was awesome and the portion was humangous. Each main course is filling enough for 2 pax.

Really good food and friendly boss. Will come back to try the fish head curry and crab soup (they've got a lot more items off menu that you can pre order in advance because they only want to cook fresh food). Had the chicken satti soru (something like claypot rice but nicer and with a kick) and mutton meal (white rice with 2 veg).

Food was really good, but the price is on the more expensive side. Spent about $170 (with taxes) for a 9 piece skewer set, Gindara Misoyaki, Ten Soba, 3 Rice set, 4 piece skewer on the side and 3 genmaicha. The Gindara (cod fish) was pleasantly sweet and the skewers especially the chicken momo was have a nice charcoal taste. The pork belly skewer was a little tough though. Some food with sauce is slightly on the stronger/saltier side (which i enjoy) so do a small sample before gobbling.
Service was generally good.
Note that some items can only be served outdoors such as the grillset.  Both indoors and outdoors seating were comfortable at night.
Not crowded when I visited but it was late (845pm). You can book before visiting and ask for either indoor or outdoor seating.

The food is good
The feel of Thailand
Haha

Love the Phay Thai‚Ä¶
Attended Chinese wedding here. Food and service is good at lower rates than most hotel banquets.

The star of Tonkatsu Special ramen is definitely the broth. 5üèÖ. Wonderfully rich bursting with meaty flavor but yet not so rich and oily to make it jilak. Ramen noodles perfectly cooked with nice bite and not clumped together. The onsen egg was also done well, soft melt in the mouth ooozze and flavor.!

The ramen is let down by the Cha shu which I personally prefer to be more well seasoned, more tender and more fat.

Overall 4 üèÖ considering the price $10.90 which is good value kopitian ramen.

Ordered egg fried rice and chicken cutlet fried rice. The rice is fragrant and tasty. Chicken cutlet is crispy but not much of flavour. What surprises us was the signature 'kong ba pau' which turns out to be good.
Good place to goüíï can really enjoy the food and environment.

waited 15 minutes for this . gravy about 30% of container, standard chicken cutlet and some plain rice (1 bowl worth) @ $5.30 (due to 30 cents for container) . Sorry to say , this is crazy . Gravy is probably prepared in advance and kept warm ( I m not sure ) . 5.00$ for plain rice , gravy and cutlet with this portion / amount at heartland is steep. Rice is not flavoured rice or Japanese rice. Just plain rice . It didn't taste Japanese.

I don't mind waiting or paying more if quality is better . To be fair , the gravy has a small amount of onion and carrots
Very friendly staff. Fast service

Was ordering a set B for lunch 2 days ago on Monday. The set comes with steam chicken, rice, side dish mushroom and lotus root soup. Potion is just nice and tasty as usual. But what stands out from my dining experience was the service. I broke the strap of my mask accidentally while trying to put it on at the end of my meal and try to re-tie it. During payment, without my mentioning about my mask, the cashier handed a new and better one to replace mine. This make my day.

Good service from Ah Liang, keep it up.
Delicious local cuisines at affordable prices. Amazing service too!

Good selection of Tai food. We tried Hor fun, basil rise and some fried eggs. The taste is good and close to authentic tai cuisine. The price is also low for the food and table service. Also to surprise dishes came with high portions. Staff is also nice and friendly, did not hesitate to help on the menu. Can become crowded during lunch hours and have to wait to get a table. Can recommend this place

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Their ayam penyet and tempeh goreng is a must try. Lots of variety.
Great dining experience. Every dish was well executed and flavourful. Highly recommended to go with friends or family. Would definitely revisit.

My favorite lok lok buffet place! It's $26.80 on weekends/public holidays and has a wide variety of items to choose from. Some items like prawns may not be the freshest but I'm not complaining because I feel overall it's worth it for the price! Many condiments to choose from to create your own dipping sauce, and drinks and ice cream also included! Can choose two soup bases and the Tom yum is my number one fav!

This place is packed during meal times. Been here countless times. Most of the stalls are pretty good. You'll get your hawker food cravings fulfilled. My personal favourites are the claypot rice & char kway teow

What a novelty that brings excitement!
We are in smiles to have a robot bringing us to our table, so cute!

We love how the food is delivered in an enclosed conveyor belt like a bullet train  zipping around and only opens up when our food is delivered to our table like a suprise box.
Thumbs up for being hygienic as I would not like to have my food, going around like old school conveyor sushi belt, uncovered and getting expose to whatever is in the air.
The service staff are attentive too.

Menu selections are very interesting, we tried lots of variety that wasn't common. It's a welcome change.

Gonna bring the kids along next time, they will be so excited over this Futuristic robot concept.

Recommend for
Large family and kids
Seats up to 6.

Will we be back?
Yes!

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Tried the Dried Black Soy Bean Sauce Noodle (Í∞ÑÏßúÏû•Î©¥) aka Dry Jjajangmyeon. Find it much better than the usual jjajangmyeon, less oily to my preference. The noodle is spongy and chewy. To go with that, we also ordered the Sweet & Sour Pork (ÌÉïÏàòÏú°). Very good! For some unknown reasons, these 2 dishes combo always appeared in korean dramas, especially after they moved house. If you like something for a change, go for the Seafood & Vegetable Platter with Mustard (ÏñëÏû•Ìîº). Its like the CNY "Loh hei", just that you are mixing and tossing thinly sliced, fresh vegetables and seafood with potato starch noodles instead.

Had such an enjoyable time at tanoke! The space was beautiful and ambiance was really nice. Special shoutout to Nareeth and chef Ken for helping me arrange a little surprise. Extremely attentive to details and needs of customers, definitely will be back! :) However, note that portions are quite small and if you have a huge appetite, the food may not be substantial.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
Food is good portion, taste average.
Person who take order has attitude problems.
Our Tim sum place at novena but there aren‚Äôt many varieties for Dim Sum. Fried rice with shrimp was nice. Icy sweet & sour pork was interesting for the 1st time but meat was normal.
My new favourite hawker western food. Pork cutlet is amazingly tasty and juicy !

Earnest and humble restaurant. It is as though you are invited to a Hakka family to enjoy a meal in their home. Delicious, authentic, generous and affordable. For those who enjoy having restaurant food that does not have a 'central kitchen / factory' taste, this is definitely a place worth trying.

The dishes we tried are:
1. ÂÆ¢ÂÆ∂‰ªòÂç∑ - Hakka Beancurd Fritters
2. ÂÆ¢ÂÆ∂ÈÖøË±ÜËÖê - Hakka Yong Tou Foo
3. Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ - Braised Pork with Preserved Vegetable
4. ËöùÊ≤πÂ•∂ÁôΩ - Nai Bai in Oyster Sauce
5. ‰∏úÊ±üÁõêÈ∏° - Steamed Chicken
6. ËêùÂçú‰∏∏ - Radish Balls

Note: Some dishes (especially the steamed chicken) may be a tad salty for some; but it's perfect for me!
An impromptu lunch.
Tried the spring chicken sometime ago, really tasty. Will visit again as i don't go there often in afternoon

Yummy food, fast service.

We ordered Assam fish head, XO prawn noodles, vinegar pig trotters, yam ring with scallops, belachan sweet potato leaves, kai lan. All the dishes were delicious, particularly the yam ring which was crispy and came with fresh vegetables too.

Price slightly on the high side, but worth the splurge.

Good:
- Axsolutely amazing service. Staffs are helpful and helped us to communicate with the bowling staffs. There were some miscomm but the staffs were sincere in apologizing and even compensated us with free soup, drinks and 10% discount even though it was not entirely their fault.

- Food portion is just nice! Prices are reasonable and 25% off for SAFRA members!

- Very nice outdoor seatings with great view of the night sky.

- Great choice of sides for the mains including aglio Olio!

Bad:
- Aglio oilio is abit salty.

Ordered prata which is served cold and hard. Vegetarian curry cold too
Ordered bee hoon goreng
Came with just bee hoon and some pieces of cabbage. Had to ask if that is all
The saving grace was the Teh halia (ginger tea) which is what this one star is for

All came up to $17. Is this expensive?

1) Assam Laksa - 1/5 Gravy was too thick and quite ‚Äúdry‚Äù , very poor customer services from the young boy.

2) Claypot chicken rice - 4/5 , quite delicious, is just the waiting time you have to bear with it during peak hour.

3) Char Kuey Teow - 2/5 , no wok hey, missing the char kuey teow fragrant. Would not recommend if you are looking for ‚Äúmalaysia taste‚Äù.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Food is nice and price is adorable. Great deal!! ü•∞

Good service. above average food. we ordered tonkatsu ebi set (the pork was well marinated and well fried). aburi saba was boneless and unique. they serve ice/warm water.  fries was pretty small portion for $6.
Consistent quality. The fish curry for prata is the best. The briyani is 1 of the best here.. love it always

Ordered the salted egg diced chicken rice which is $6 on their menu but was charged $7 and had to pay another 70¬¢ for the egg which usually came with it.

Apparently it is only $6 during the "lunch promotion" but nobody informed me when I ordered. I'm ok with paying more but I wished that this was clarified before I was charged for the food.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
This hawker centre is one of the best hawkers in Singapore. Many awarded & featured hawker stores from various online platform as well as newspaper outlets.

Some of the famous stores here include this white carrot cake store ( for $4 theres a generous portion of egg. The texture on the outside is crispy & soft on the inside chilli sauce is slightly on the sweeter side & not too spicy for those who can't stand the heat)

Hokkien mee ($8 portion in the picture. Get 5 small prawns which are peeled for you & no fishy smell for the sotong n prawn. This will be the wetter version of hokkien mee. It's a good plate but only thing lacking is more char flavour or wokhei.)

Many other food here not in the picture but are delicious !!!!

5 stars for the friendly service. Like the cosy environment too. tried the duck confit tender meat but overall its too salty for me. The pork redeye on the other hand is delicious though.
It is a place you don't mind to say ' I'll be back'
üòä

On the contrary to most reviewers, attendants were attentive BUT VERY CONFUSED.. That was mostly about the orders and availability of dishes, the rest of the dinner was well enjoyed..
Food was delicious and the fish steamboat we came for was delectable (I would hope so, given the price). Not to forget, they are opened 24 hours, I can come at any hour when I miss the soup..
Fantastic food and fantastically priced. Authentic Thai food cooked by Thais. Highly recommended!!

Went on Sunday 6.30pm, but was informed that the 250g ribeye is not available only 180g left, banana split has blackened refrigerated bananas and could not be served, we had to remind them to serve the wine that we ordered. They accidentally added a $25 takeaway item to my table and she didn't seem to believe me when I said we didn't order it. She even asked others from my table if they ordered and refused to take it off the bill until another server told her it was for another table. The restaurant was not even full. Quite disappointing experience.

C.C.B was my favourite dish! Head down to the cafe to find out what I mean üòâ

Attracted to the amazing ambience of this cafe! I highly recommend all of you to have a sense of it too!

- Food; EXCELLENT!! ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è The food display was exquisite, the food taste just as pleasant as how it looks (I took video instead of photos, cant post it)

- Chill outdoor; can bring your pet along, I saw one doggo üòç (it‚Äôs open 24/7 according to one of the bosses)

- Cozy indoor; the furnishing of the cafe felt like I was in a HIGH END restaurant with affordable food, there are high chairs, sofas, and other different types of sitting to choose from (closes at 10-10.30pm)

Hi...are you planning to take the tel line to explore this place or cycling past as I was? I'm flabbergasted by the reviews here. The masala thosai I ordered (chef's recommendation) was extremely poor. Sorry for the half eaten picture(as I was starving) but you can see from the pic the potatoes were so poor. The coffee was extremely watery too despite the change. What about the other chef recommendations? I'm just so shocked the standards have dropped.

I was a regular here, Food is good but as time flies by my favourite orders are always(!) out of stock (Mango sticky rice, fried prawn cake) and today coke was out of stock too. Service is tremendously bad :) singaporean lady with black specs was absolutely rude, banging the fridge door, raising her voice telling us to take a smaller table, almost shouting at us to speak louder as she says she cant hear us:) the way she spoke to us was literally telling us that she‚Äôs unhappy having us here, totally fed up. Came in with a good mood but everything deteriorated after experiencing their worst service. Pretty sure the owners here dont really care about their work attitude as i have heard my friends saying it gets worse as time flies by.

Milk tea made from sugar.. damn sweet... diluted sweet. Like a syrup drinks. no Thai tea fragrance. I order phai tai, is like eating dessert.. so sweet... all noodle Lump up together.. üòì food are very salty.

Is the worst phai tai I ever ate. If is not because of convenience, I won‚Äôt come, never again. Not worth the $.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: The food are delicious, not expensive, served in large portions. Suitable for family.

This is a nice cosy place with attentive service.  I had a fish and chips which was not bad at all. The pricing is typical of caf√©s of this type.

The location is great and it has a nice view of Thomson Road and people walking by.

If you were in the neighbourhood and wanted a meal, this would be a ideal place for a family meal. Recommended.

No wonder every morning super long queue.
The Green nasi lemak (coconut rice) very tasty and the portion is very generous for $3 (one fried fish, one fried chicken wing, omelette and fried anchovies with peanuts. So TASTY la üòã
MUST TRY!!!!!
The two types of epok2 (curry puff), sardine and potatoes also VERY TASTY üòã
Lovely place for family and friends. Very accommodating staffs, tasty food and great drinks üç∫  We will surely recommend this place.

I came here with my elderly parents and my wheelchair dependent sister for dinner. The entrance to their dining area is not wheelchair friendly but insisted that they are not opening the adjacent dinning room that has a ramp. So I ask for a chair with a back rest so that I can slowly move my sister to be seated on a chair. Unfortunately, I was told that they don't have any. What restaurant at this time and age not handicap friendly and neither are the staff helpful with our plight. What a disappointment regardless of their acceptably good food.

Nice place for local fare though prices are a little on the high end for things like prata. The chicken curry is nice though the chicken taste like frozen chicken - fresh chicken would have taste better.

Ordered via Grab, just a salad. Not bad, cannot comment much as the main dishes are still maki rolls which I did not ordered.  Salad has many choices of sides to choose from. The only thing is I wish the portion could be bigger.
Nasi lemak original set, simple yet fragrance rice n sambal chilli, a great breakfast meal to start the fay!
Variety of menu to choose from. Friendly staff. Able to accept NETS.

The chendol here increaeed to $2.50 but still is much better than most others.
Like the carrot cake with bean sprouts and a bit of lard crisp, may need to wait for 10mins if they are doing fried prawn noodles...
The taste of the mee rebus is competent, there is not much ingredients. Ok for $3.50...
Tried the ipoh yong tau foo - not bad curry was thick and flavourful but a but pricy for ytf...
Teenager remarked that the ice kang at $2.50 was more worthwhile than chendol... heehee
Between the first dish & white rice served, there was a 20 mins gap before the rest of the dishes came! We had expected much better from a Chinese restaurant in an award-winning establishment.
One of the nice underrated food stall at AMK Central. The food selection is Nasi Pasang. Price is reasonable and quality is good.

The food quality is good , fresh prawns used so that‚Äôs important for me. The mee sua (noodle) dish is a must have . Really yummy . If u order medium it‚Äôs good for 3 person , worth the money I must say . Love the century egg with wood ear .  Kudos to the chef there. Enjoyed my lunch !

The taste is almost 90% similar to last time.. but it's good enough for me to give 5 stars.. maybe give auntie/uncle warm up for like 1 month then the taste will be 100% the same..

Very value for money and nice.. but expect around 30min wait during meals time..

The distance is the same as walking from amk hub to the s11 coffee shop..

Please do support the uncles and aunties

First time going to buffet shop, what u order u won't get it. First ask the waitress y we order so much and come out only this few they told us still preparing please wait as the shop had a lot of customer. After eating n waiting for one hour plus we saw quite a lot had left or sitting down chit chat so we decided to order one last round before settings the bill. We felt very disappointed what we order not even half of it come and the staff already cleaning or prepare to close shop kind of attitude. So what I think if u worry people eat a lot please don come out do buffet
Absolutely stunning decor. Food was delicious üòã

Cheap and delicious!! The space is a little bit small so if coming in group of more than 2 person, high chance will have to wait a while as there are limited seats for bigger groups , but the staffs are super friendly and nice!

Their ice flavoured tea is good, along with the Pearl, which is probably better than the ones at Koi HAHAHA
Expensive and really bad tasting food. Don‚Äôt bother calling it ‚ÄúMalaysian‚Äù food, standard is really incomparable to authentic in M‚Äôsia.
Perfect sardine satti soru... so far the best in Singapore that I had. Dessert not reccomended for those are in budget as price is similar to main meal ~12$

The food here is top notch, every dish carefully thought through. The Japanese Fruit Tomato dish was layered with multiple flavour bombs, simple but delicious! Extremely great service provided by Nareenth who really made the dining experience very enjoyable!

Pratas are crispy, but the curry sauce dip didn't impress. So if really want to try, don't take away. Only do dine-in for the crispy texture.

Tried the mutton biryani and it's not to my taste. The mutton is good (tender, juicy) with a favour full sauce, but my taste buds just doesn't exclaim with joy.

Return rating 6
Solid Thai food - couldn‚Äôt travel but got my fix here. Highly recommend!
Not the original place but taste the same. Price of various pratas are ok, but specialty ones are quite ex. Their rice are quite tasty too. No windows in the place though, so it's quite stuffy.
Place is nice and classy. Service is  really excellent. Only the food was very disappointing. I hope they will improve on the taste.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Food is good, the place abit too noisy for a proper conversation with friends. Please check your receipt. Went there 3 times, and coincidentally there‚Äôs extra dishes added to the bill every time , don‚Äôt pay extra for nothing

Ordered via Grab Delivery, the menu said the Bara Chirashi had swordfish and salmon roe in it. When I received it there was only half a small cube of swordfish, and no salmon roe at all. That's pretty much lying. Taste wise was ok.

Casual dinner with a couple of friends.
Had the teppanyaki beef set (changed rice to garlic fried rice), chicken chahan, mentaiko okonomiyaki, koebi and a few more dishes like salmon sashimi and sushi. Happy that we're able to order from sister restaurant Tamako Meal!

Price very reasonable, friendly staff, 10/10 will come again üëèüèª

P.s. parking might be hard over the weekends.

I haven't been here for many years... But I definitely know standard has dropped and the famous fish and chips now tastes different, their garlic bread was hard and dry I didn't even know I was eating bread?!... Hope they can get back their original standard...

The teh was nice. The normal basic prata or masala prata was good serve with 2 dip curry and ikan bilis  sambal. The murtabak came well presented but sad to say one of the worst I have tasted. One side was badly burnt and hard unable to cut through. The top was lightly fried and soft . Boiled mince mutton without much marination was added in it . Second slice I really feel yucky even though I have submerge each bite piece into the curry. The chicken curry was a little diluted , taste of curry leaf and powder not much spices and punch in their curry.
Worst food, not worth for price.. quality is very worst.. I don‚Äôt recommend to go this place again..
Nice food in shop house with no aircon. Price good because no additon GST and service charge. üòî
Lovely lovely Nasi Padang in Toa Payoh. Great flavour and Chili. The sotong is really fresh and well cooked!

Very good service. Crowd is a mix of posh and pro.
Brunch on a Sunday isn't crowded here and just the right time for chillax after eating. Must try adobo here! üáµüá≠üëçüòé

Ordered the power mee rebus after seeing a recommendation from a friend. It was yummy! Highlight was the sauce ü§§ will be back to try the satay (only starts at 3:30pm) and Soto (pictured here but it wasn‚Äôt mine).

Also, expect long queues!
Food is not bad, cheap but be prepared to wait...gets crowded and also does a lot of deliveries.
Famous for their $1 nasi lemak which is light on the wallet and a great taste of old-school. Likewise for their mee rebus, mee siam & lontong.

What a fall from grace. Used to be very famous and delicious in the 90s and 00s. The prata was very oily which made them very gelat. The cheese naan.....practically had no cheese. So not sure what they served us. Drinks were rather bland. No wonder there wasn't any crowd on that Saturday evening.
Very horrible food. Sri sun at Blk 291 Yishun is way better.

Great new place. Food is delicious with reasonable prices. Has a bit of a homestyle feel with relaxed but friendly service.
Currently has a discount of 10% for Northpoint residents.
Have not had a bad dish yet after three trips!
Food is on point and in-line with the 313 Tung Lok restaurant. Peking duck is excellent. Come and support the team.

The red meat plate are good for affordable price. The entries and the desserts so so (rather close to company' cantine than French basic p√¢tisseries from street' corner).   For entries and desserts, rather feel like eating ibis budget hotel than novotel for those who know. Mains really worse it however. So overall as it is cheap it's OK for quick lunch or dinner.
Peace n relax not hurry
The beef rendang is very tender!!! Not too sweet and very tasty!

Ridiculous rules about no seating before everyone arrived - even though we offered to order and start eating first and the restaurant was not even halfway full. Stubborn and rude staff who refuse to budge - guess they prefer to have 0 customers over even just 2?

Overall, food and service quality have been declining over the past few years - waiting times for food grow longer, orders get messed up, and tables get ignored or have their order sheet misplaced entirely.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: I have eaten at Wee Nam Kee for more than 10 years and I loved the chicken, the rice and the condiments. Unfortunately, this time I didn't quite enjoy the meal. Perhaps I should not say why as the taste for food is very subjective.
Unhealthy food, don't crave too much.

The food are not bad but they are not consistent in their service, for example, Nasi Briyani usually comes with the papadum but some days they don't give (not that they don't have). They charged me $2 more than their menu just now. His face looked threatening and insisted that he is correct. When I told him that the menu mentioned otherwise, he told me to look again. I didn't because I would rather let him overcharged and not patronize that restaurant in future.

Came here in the afternoon and had the set lunch. The pork and ginger is recommended. It comes with a soft boiled egg which when poured over the rice really makes the dish quite nice. Prices are on the high end. It is set in a park and there is ample parking nearby.

A Hot Hideout @ NTU
Yummy yummy mala selling here!  The collagen soup is delicious too! Very different with the mala in other parts of Singapore! Must try! Highly recommended! I wish I could add six stars üëçüëçüëç
Affordable western food in Toa Payoh MRT station, not very crowded even Friday evening
Tomato soup base is rich and flavourful. Sevice is great.
The soup ipoh hor fun was quite good, but everything else was just average. They close quite early at 8pm as well.
4 stars for the nuggets and fried chicken wings.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Not worth the $82 for 2 pax for the Xiao Long Bao buffet b'cos they took a long time to serve only 2 trays (6 pcs each tray) per order. What kind of buffet that set such ordering limit?

You have to keep chasing "what's happening to my XLB?". It looks like they prefer that you filled your stomach with their 2 complementary bowls of la mien and a side dish which you are not allow reject.

After long waiting in between orders, you begin to feel full and your marginal utility drop drastically and hence lost appetite for more XLB.

So be careful not to fall for this type of promotional gimmick which wasn't sincere at all.

Writing them off after this bad experience. Sigh !!!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Would have given a 5 star but some of the staff were quite rude. Inexpensive and the meat was well marinated.

All dishes are yummy tonight!

Food tastes are much better than delivery. This branch location is convenient. Just a straight walk after exit MRT station.

Maybe it is only me. the broth is salty, not thick and feels like instant japanese ramen. Too pricey for instant ramen standard and the taste is not in par with keisuke imo. The place is also crowded af, all table are chopped by uncle.

Ordered tonkatsu ramen. The noodle is pretty Q and nice. The soup is bland. The meat is dry and tbh quite tasteless. It‚Äôs affordable though. Definitely cannot compare with other cheap ramen that are more flavourful.

Excellent place for having the Pequim Duck.
People very nice and polite. Lovely place

If you are looking for authentic Cantonese dishes, this is one restaurant that you would want to be in your list to check out. I use of my own photo and some from their site as the dishes was eaten too fast by my family. Love their roasted crispy pork! It's really awesome, must order! We order the longevity bun in advance as we are celebrating our mother's birthday. Which is better than those i had as theirs are handmade with nice warm, not so sweet pure lotus paste. Well, i could go on for more but go try it yourself. Oh! last thing, portion are big if you order medium like me.

Food good only do not understand why the gravy are being charged $1.00 with portion given are sometimes too much ending up throwing away. Rather they do not charge for the gravy and give appropriate portion rather than going to waste on efforts cooked.

Our first time experience to try the main. Food is really great and service staff is friendly and attentive. Wide selection of food from snacks to main course. Great for tea break or proper meals.  The place is clean and deco is retro so quite interesting. Peak hours can be packed so do go slightly early before the peak. Their coconut buns and curry buns is a must try too!

Food was good. Ordered the drunken chicken (cold dish), duck fried with some wrap (was oily), the Signature xiaolongbao (good), shrimp and bamboo shoot noodle (hardly any bamboo shoot). Friend said the fried rice with pork chop was good and really worth the price.
We were seated near the entrance so service not great cos the wait staff were usually not looking at our table. But once we got their attention they were good.

Enjoyed the Jing Tai Lan steamboat, which came with large, fresh slices of red grouper and lots of vegetables. The only issue was that the the broth could have had a deeper, more natural flavour. The Teochew oyster omelette was great with large oysters and a good number of them. The nai bai was fine.

Very friendly stall owners, everything is handmade. It's $4 for a regular, $5 for a large bowl, the ingredients are definitely of good quality and they sell out by 12.30pm ish so be sure to get there early, I went there at 12pm for 3 days and they were all out. The noodles are made locally and their chilli packs a punch

Standard tasting stuff at a steep price. Ordered via Grab. Extra charges apply.

Fried Rice with Eggs($9.90)
Fried Rice with Shredded Pork & Eggs($12.50)
Fried Rice with Pork Chop($15.30)
Noodle with Minced Pork in Bean Sauce($11.90)

After a 2 year break (thanks COVID) had a chance to try this again. Have to say I am very disappointed as the price vs quality and quantity has dropped by so much. There is much better fare to spend your $ and appetite on in this place
efficient service
For now , no matter what you order, you aren‚Äôt disappointed. It‚Äôs not particularly tasty but it‚Äôs not bad.
Yummy!

Did not patronise but was at Djitsun mall today and saw a member of staff wearing her apron into the toilet cubicle. After coming out she left the toilet without washing her hands. Disgusting standards of personal hygiene. Plus f&b staff are generally not supposed to wear aprons to the bathrooms - how could they allow that?

Juicy gyoza, xiaolongbao, chinese pizza, xiumai, spring roll and variety of dim sum for reasonable price. Frozen dim sum is also available for take away.
Spring roll was very very hot. Be careful!!

Good variety of dishes, from appetizers to mains. Quality and taste of most of their food are above average. A few items l'll always order when l'm there are their mushroom soup, angus beef and seafood risotto. Another couple of positives are their fast and efficient service and  reasonable prices.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Went with group of my friends . we had variety s of Indian vegetarian food it's very delicious üòã yummy... Even thow very bc they did very good customer service.
A really chill place with many other shops nearby, the food was great and service was even btr

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Quality and taste of food very nice

The food here is OK. You can have them fried the item you want or cook it yourself in the soup of your choice. If you plan to eat a lot, you can go for unlimited stick and it comes with drink and ice  cream
Your daily mamak meal fix. Personal favourite will be the thosai and murtabak sardine.

The lunch specials are quite a fair deal. The chicken in the biryani was good, although the rice wasn‚Äôt as fragrant or flavourful as it could be. The Prata Them All set was a hefty portion, as was the mini Ultimate Murtabak (can‚Äôt imagine what the regular size would be!). All considerably tasty and good value.

However, what I recommend is the plain prata‚Äîcrispy and delicious without being overly oily. Sometimes simplest is best. I accompanied it with curry mutton and seasonal vegetables from the √† la carte menu, though I would try something else, as the mutton was chewy and the vegetables (eggplant) absorbed too much oil. Regardless, flavours were palatable.

I had my first ever teh tarik, which was aromatic and sweetened just the right amount. Overall, a satisfactory meal. I‚Äôm glad to have found some good prata nearby. Next time, we will have to order conservatively because the food was heavy.

Went here for a quick lunch from office, around 10 of us. Got in early so got food fast, there was quite a waiting when we were leaving.
The food itself was good, I had the teriyaki salmon. The service was very good, I had a special request and they remembered it even with all the rush.

Stood at the waiting line around 5pm, nobody was there to serve us for quite some time. The service not up to standard. Most of the dishes were served either warm or cold, only the green tea was hot, everything here was underwhelming. Total damage $85++

Happy with food and drink ordered. But wasn't impressed with the cashier staff who cleared tables, and swept crumbs and bits onto the floor instead of clearing it up properly. He even flicked the table cloth so that allthe stuff collected on it goes onto the floor!

Eye sore when you are eating and you see the dirtied floor and smashed food cos people stepped on it.

amazing gyudon soaked in oil.... how does anyone deserved to be served this? this is not how gyudon is served in japan either.
hoping this is a mistake, may try again but can‚Äôt say I want to for S$11.

The place is alright I Guess if you are in the neighbourhood and wants to eat Penang food. It is no difference in hawker centre food. While the fried kway Tiao is not oily, it is also very bland. The Penang laksa tasted better but not as favourful as expected. The prawn noodle I believe it‚Äôs a murdering tool, who puts a big pile of chilli in a small bowl of food. The chendol definitely can skip. Take note this is a cash term only shop.

Wide range of Malaysian food from popular tourist spots. Food taste okay and slightly resemble Malaysia's. For those craving for Malaysian food, can try it here. Try to avoid peak hours such as lunch or dinner hours because it's similar to foodcourt and your have to "chop" your own seats. üòÇ

Great food and service. We had great experience there.

Xiao long baos were juicy with super delicate skins thin, a little elastic and soft.

There isn‚Äôt by government regulations and there no guest except me. It‚Äôs hot and no chair outside , I‚Äôll never go back‚Ä¶

Service Bad. attitude is terrible.
Their Restaurant At Amk Dijtsun Mall. ytd i take away Mala xiang guo. While i  was eating I found that inside the food got a piece of rubber band. I came to exchange but staff didnt say sorry. the 2nd time still got the rubber band. so i told them. But all staff showed the black  face and told me "You come again?". "The rubber band doesn't belong to us, it is your rubber band. We dont have that kind of rubber band". Omg! I just bought only. Their attitude was like I owe them money. That's unacceptable. Please look in to it seriously if u still want to continue the business in this COVID 19.  U noe This issue i can report ur restaurant To NEA

Great concept of bringing affordable yakiniku to the masses. Menu can come across as beef heavy although lamb, chicken, and seafood options are available. Wagyu is available. Ingredients are fresh but portion is small. Grilling is diy and smoke control is pretty good. Service crews were attentive.
Cosy & relax restaurant Thai Kway Chap since 2014 highly recommended served in claypot top it up with a cup of Thai milk tea to sweeten your day
Prawn noodle was not bad but lor mee so so only

Very tasty chinese food. French bean(Âπ≤ÊâÅÂõõÂ≠£Ë±Ü)in particular was the best I have ever had. Also ordered their Zhenjiang Pork Rib (ÈïáÊ±üÊéíÈ™®) and Poached Sliced Beef in Spicy Sauce (Ê∞¥ÁÖÆÁâõËÇâ) which were both very good as well. Overall a very enjoyable meal.
Love their fried chicken. It's real good

Food was great. We started with the tomato, it was refreshing, mildly sweet and a little tart, a great way to whet your appetite at the start of the meal. The beef was really really good, topped with fried slices of garlic, roasted like a teppanyaki style. Overall all the dishes were good, overall a very enjoyable range of food. The desserts were not overly sweet, balanced and a great way to leave the meal without feeling too heavy. The service was really good.

The ambience was really nice, modern without being too cold. My only critique is a lack of ambient music to set the mood.

Regarding the service, I guess much of the reviews were from a long time ago, but my experience here was amazing. The staff was attentive and anticipates your needs. We went for a birthday and when we needed the cake, we only needed to look at the staff and the Caucasian staff immediately understood. And even suggested the right portion of desserts for our party. Really appreciate his attitude and level of service. Salute.

Highly recommended place.
Great, authentic Japanese food served in a homely environment.

New experience with Thai food.. Nice taste of each dishes... Suggested the Green Curry very delicious. Pineapple rice is a must into the dinner...
Favolous taste is dessert D1 made with sago and cocco, a taste never try, wonderfull..
Worst service ever. The sever in black is rude and should not be in service line. A simple request of asking a plastic seems a big deal for her. Slam my food on the glass counter.
Old school dim sum house with waitresses pushing dim sum carts around. Taste is avg.
Food are nice and price are cheap!!!
Nice and affordable breakfast and lunch place!!! You are also able to customize your noodles (though I felt like trying their rice instead). Will be back to try their cross-bridge noodles üòÅ
Value for money and doesn't disappoint!
Decent..

Decent prices n good local food.
Staff are rude n impatient however can get on after payment n dig into your meal right after. Ample seats around a break from shopping.
Not bad. With good Dum briyani and local dishes. Halal. Clean.
Japanese food

Delicious food and tastes authentic
üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªstaff are also very patient
Did a takeaway for the sushi and not disappointed. Fresh and reasonably priced, with many varieties to choose from. Spoilt for choice!
I find the portion is big if you eat there compare to packet..price reasonable.

Select Group Cloud Kitchen opened within Grains & Hops on 29 May 2021, at #02-01. Basically they took up 4 stall space and offer delivery/takeaway for 7 brands (see pictures for brands available).

Ordering can be done through the 2 kiosks available, payment only by Nets. For customers who may need help, there is a counter where you can place order with staff but payment also by Nets only.

Once order is ready (you can order from any combination of stalls), you will get a receipt with a number, look out for your number on display and then collect from the numbered locker.

How to get there: bus stop after mosque along Braddell Road, just in front of Blk 978 Toa Payoh North building. Grain & Hop is on level 2, access by escalator (see picture).

If driving, you can park at the MSCP within blk 978, as open air car park mainly for season (but on Sunday quite empty). Alternative is to park at Blk 199 Toa Payoh North open air carpark just behind the industrial estate, short 5 min walk.

Enjoy!

Worst place ever! Took so long to make my two prata and when I asked for it shown me stupid face and asked me again what‚Äôs my orders like a gangster.(the younger staff). I have been here for many years all elderly staff don‚Äôt do that. That‚Äôs 7am and the Coffeeshop really not so busy yet, if u not happy don‚Äôt sell here.Refused to give me curry and I have to ask for it! Prata don‚Äôt come with curry??? The Rivervale crescent branch (Seng Kang) Blk 178.
Nice hor fun. Love it. Really crowded tonight. Incredibly popular. Simply because they serve really good dishes. Really good.
Cosy environment. They do sell beers at night. If you prefer quiet place with some decent foods, this could be your choice. They are located at industrial area.

Visited this outlet yesterday to try their ramen. The prices are really more affordable than usual ramen restaurants. Generous portions given for all noodles and free extra noodles too!

The broth is not bad, not too oily imho while the char shu is average, although they do put in a lot of pieces :)

Ichiban Sushi is one of my fav sushi place.Aaahh their salmon mental sushi is one of their new dish and its just so delicious and pleasurable. Beautiful ambiance and the prices are affordable. You can eat everything here and they provide big meals‚ò∫Ô∏èTruly perfect for me and my friend‚ù§Ô∏èDefinitely will recommend it and see you again‚ù§Ô∏è

good food, but when order thru online food apps, rejects the order after confirmation at the door step for self collection.
Poor customer service

Was once the old Mikkeller bar before covid hit.
Now it same floors brings new exciting food and beverage paring adventures.
