content:
Solid flavourful maggie goreng mutton and teh o ice.

Supremely good supper place. Will be back 24/7!
Very nice

Great food from both outlets but the one at the s11 got some rude stall assistant ,ask him what time they opening(I was there at 12pm) ,he just no open rudely,n shoo me away ,from that day ,I just go to the one opp the AMK mall ,where the old stall assistant moved to n for the food ,go for the sunny egg fried rice, spring chicken n both the chicken n pork chops r great

1st visit giving bad experience to me and my wife. ordered the drink doesn‚Äôt deliver to us. The staff was told us we ordered 3 food with 1 drink. My order is 2 food and 2 drink. She didn‚Äôt check my order and listen wrongly. The kitchen staff giving that kind of eyes contact to us which make us feel like we are wrong at 1st. if possible i will give 0 star to this outlet.

Wow very nice. Authentic taste at 3am. Got the Takagi ramen. Close to Tonkotsu. Very nice broth. Chashu a bit thin like ham, but for $6 how to complain. Super value.

Venue a bit tight but ok. If you go late the tray collector thing gets filled so old soup bowls overflowing.

Got ePay but nets only. Parking‚Äôs a bit far unless gamble right up front.

Went on a weekday afternoon for lunch, not much crowd on a weekday. This cafe is quite spacious, have an outdoor and indoor seating area. I ordered the Chicken waffles Chicken was tender and delicious. The only complain was quite warm indoor, seem like the air-conditional is not working. Overall, wonderful place to chill and will visit again.
Fresh, beautifully prepared and great variety.
Probably the best mala hotpot.

These guys are super rude and arrogant. Both the younger and old guys are rude to the customers. First off the nasi lemak is just average but sometimes there is a queue. I think he has enough business and that made him very arrogant and atrocious. Bad service and very bad attitude.

Pin Hsiang Family Restaurant is an air-conditioned place where my family often goes to for affordable and tasty meals.

The prawn rolls are crispy and goes well with the sweet dark sauce. The texture of the omelette is nice and it's one of my favourite dish. Fish is served with mushroom but the taste is slightly on the bland side. Broccoli with scallops are ok. They served homemade barley. The rice portion is on the high side for me to finish one plate. You can consider sharing the rice if you are not a big eater.

Service of staff is merely taking orders and serving which could be improved simply by giving a smile to customers.

#ILovePinHsiangFamilyRestaurant
Good taste nasikemak, wonderful breakfast

Soup is rich and tasty, but uncle was extremely rude. I queued up at 12:30 pm (lunch time) and ordered 4 portions of prawn mee to go. He told me in chinese language that 4 portions will jam up the queue behind me and shouted to the 3 people behind ‚Äòyou got to wait because she ordered 4 portions‚Äô. I felt embarrassed. Now looking back, shouldn‚Äôt you expect such orders in the F and B industry? Are you sure you want to treat your patrons who support your business this way? Such an attitude was off-putting and destroyed my appetite. I would not be buying my prawn mee from this place again.

I came back for this bowl. Probably the only competent chili ban mee in the area. Toothsome noodles, topped up for extra veg and the amount was generous.

Unfortunately I won't be back save for at odd hours. Queue management is terrible for this stall. I wasn't given a buzzer or any indication of when my food might be ready, so I hovered at the counter, getting more and more demoralised with every order that wasn't mine. It's good but not enough to warrant a 20 mintue wait. There weren't enough seats on a weekday at lunch either.

Pandan waffle is dense and kueh like. That suits me fine. The blueberry spread is a no go unless you want diabetes.

A very healthy choice of Yong Tau Fong here.  Soup is not overly salty but sufficiently savory to the taste bug. üëçüèªüëçüèª

My second visit with 3 pax. We tried out the char pot rice, KL Hokkien mee and last the oyster omelette. The best I liked is the oyster    omelette. Each bite of it comes with a flavorful taste. The stall selling both the oyster omelette and pork noodle. So do expect some waiting time.

For 3 of us, we ordered the pork ribs, sambal kangkong and clay pot bean curd with 3 rice. Total $29.10 ... I like that they deep fry the pork ribs first then coat with savoury sweet sour sauce. The sambal kangkong was also delicious. Fried with enough "haebi" giving it a robust sambal belachan taste. I've eaten the same stuff elsewhere but it was another level up over here.  Highly recommended. Sorry for not having photos as we walloped the food and then realising after that we should have.

Coffee rib is tasty! Food prices if have discounts, is acceptable. Food in general not bad but beware the portions only come in family size portion. Can be too much, given the 2 pax covid dining restrictions now.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Good food.. affordable price
If u want awesome porridge,u gt to come here!

Visited the place on a weekday afternoon and was delighted that there‚Äôs no crowd. Huge space with ample seating area. Had the fried chicken, sakura pasta and the creamed corn (CCB).

The pasta and chicken were great but the corn was just alright. The sour cream was not a good addition to the corn. Drinks were on the expensive side too.

My second time back at the Toa Payoh branch, i was surprised that the waitress recognised and greeted me like an long time customer. Was recommended to try their steam fish with lime sauce. Me and my girlfriend like it very much. Thank you for the friendly gesture
and great recommendation. I will be back to try other dishes. üòÑ

To be fair, I find it quite difficult to award 5 stars for take-aways as food quality is usually compromised during travelling but this restaurant deserves at least 4.5 stars. My family loves the deep-fried pork belly with fermented beancurd with garlic skin on. The noodles were a little on the bland side but that's okay because chilli padi and sambal sauces were given to complement the taste. The wok fried squid with chinchalok is a unique item on any zi char menu!
Very nice place, clean and bright. The lady boss was very kind and thoughtful. Kept checking on us throughout the nite. Food was decent and will solve your cravings for Malaysian food.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Food so good, the owner is so nice n hospitable. He speaks English well. We paid $20 for 2 sets.
Satisfied with this!
Arrived here 9.40pm but was told last order already despite the operating hour states until 10:30.  Wasted the effort to travel all the way here ü•≤ will try my luck again next time
Located at B1 near the end of the Japanese Street food section. Waiting time not too bad if before or after the peak hours. Just wish they had free flow cold green tea

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Had a family dinner here for 10 pax. Entering the restaurant was painless after reservations made earlier.
Service - I was disappointed with the lack of attention to our table and the very slow drip of replenishment food which we had ordered through the website. Initial round of meats and other condiments served barely covered the amount of people we had in our table which resulted in each person only having a piece of meat before running out. We had to order again through the website ordering system and waited more than 20 mins for them to actually give us more food. Regrettably this only happened after I had to literally chase down a staff at the other end of the place and complain.By the way I don't blame the staff for the restaurant being clearly short handed.
Foodwise the quality given was average at best which did not match the asking price for a buffet . For reference per head we were charged SGD 35++ per adult not inclusive of an additional optional charge of SGD4.90 ++ for free flow drinks / desserts. For that price in comparison would have expected prawns to be available but this was only available if you add a further charge for premium meat/seafood. which would have brought the price up per head to SGD 50++.You could get a buffet with oysters / prawn at a hotel at that price.
In conclusion I would not recommend the restaurant at this moment due to food quality versus price asked.

(Translated by Google) Super crispy coin prata and the Gao pull! ‚Åá

(Original)
Super crispy coin prata and teh tarik Gao! üòãüòã

Have been a regular at the stall especially enjoyed their claypot tofu which comes with lots of gravy. First time ordered delivery as my whole family down with Covid-19 and they willing agree to deliver despite knowing our conditions. Thanks so much!
Mainly Shanghai dumplings ( steam and pan fried ). Stir fried vegetables is delicious but the noodles is a bit sweet.

Due to the Covid-19 situation we tried their take-away menu and it was absolutely fantastic.
We could taste the care about ingredients, the research behind every plate. A selection of the very best of Chinese/Thai cuisine. Very happy.

Tried the 1 for 1 don. It's delicious n nicely packed for takeaway. We opted for the unagi don and a big piece of unagi was given.The food was still warm upon correction eventhough I pre-ordered and was late for collection. The staff was also very helpful and friendly to double confirm my order, providing good direction of the place and bringing the food and credit card terminal out so that I don't need to step into the restaurant and do safe entry. üëçüëç

Had a fantastic breakfast here as part of our staycation. Everything is lovingly made in house from their croissants (SO good!) to their hollandaise and English muffins. The coffee is also excellent. Service was top notch, too, kudos to the kind and professional team! Only regret is we devoured the eggs Benedict before we could take a pic :) it comes with a hearty portion of prosciutto and spinach and was served with perfectly poached eggs.

This old school western food stall located in AMK Central Market, has been around for years. They sell affordable old fashioned western food like chicken cutlet, fish & chips, mixed grill with sides baked beans, fries and salad.

Their mains are served in generous huge portion, covering almost half the size of the plate, which you can see from the pictures. Fried with a crispy outer layer, the meat within is thick and filling too. It brings back wonderful childhood memories of myself, eating plates of oversized chicken cutlet with same cheap side dishes like canned beans and coleslaw.

Their food is wallet friendly and definitely worth the try.
Reasonable prices great food. Pleasant environment for a Thai food. Dinner time could be quite crowded.

Ordered steam sea bass , kangkong, prawn cake and tomyun with 3 rices.
Cost $50
Fresh and tasty. One of the thai stall that I will patronize often.

$18.90 Unagi Set Meal (After Taxes ~$23)
Took ~ 15 mins to Prepare (non-peak hour)
Service (7/10) waitress was friendly

Unagi - (7/10) Acceptable Portion and Standard
Ebi - (5/10) Meh. Like Food Court Japanese store standard
Rice (5/10) just your normal rice or u could add $2 upgrade to ‚Äúsushi rice‚Äù
Miso Soup (5/10) standard not outstanding

Unlikely to come back again as there are better options at this price point.

A hidden gem on par with BIAP - this place is easily overlooked with a hole-in-the-wall entrance nestled between seemingly grander food options and we were really surprised by how it opens up to an unexpectedly spacious and cavernous dining area. The pork bone soup tasted EXACTLY like BIAP‚Äôs collagen soup and they even had the signature bean curd rolls?! With their 3-5pm 40% off it‚Äôs like getting BIAP for half the price. Everything we got was amazing as always for a restaurant under the paradise group; must order items include the bean curd roll, ebiko prawn paste and ramen.

Coming back for the 4th time on 28/3/22. Our staples for 3 ppl include:
- 1 portion of beef
- 1/2 portion of pork belly
- mushrooms: oyster, enoki, king oyster (not recommended to get shimeji as they swim around n get lost in the soup)
- pork and chive dumpling
- ebiko prawn paste
- 2 x ramen
- bean curd skin roll
- veggies: cabbage, tang-o
- condiments! My personal fav includes vinegar, soy sauce, chili oil, garlic, spring onions and parsley.
Great food and prices, great and fast services, have vegetarian choices, all curry and chilli tastes great

Favourite food from Jack‚Äôs Place is its potato jacket with cream and bacon bits. Cheese fries were not too bad, chunky fries were crispy. Other than that, Salted Egg Chicken Cutlet was oily and not the most delicious salted egg sauce around. Buffalo wings had a strange taste. Panna Cotta dessert looked more like a mousse cake.

Thank you Alan. Very polite, friendly and offered us with good recommendation. Service was good. Food was served hot, fast was delicious. Really like how they use the serving belt to deliver the food. Very efficient and effective. Thank you.
Tried Oishi Beef Udon. Yummy.

Just for 14Jun's order. We made an order today and found the batter for the fried fish n spaghetti too salty. Not sure if the spaghetti was boiled too long in salt water or the sauce over salted. Had to remove the batter from the dory fish for consumption. No issues with previous orders. Perhaps the cook could be more mindful. Thank you.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Waiting time too long and will always mess up our order. Once the place is crowded, you have keep asking where's ur order cos they will forget about it

Had the aglio olio but it was unfortunately super salty. The taste was still not too bad i guess, if I ignore the salt, and the price of $4.50 is pretty affordable for a plate of aglio olio. The egg is also a really nice touch! They just gotta take it easy with salting the dish it'll be alright.

Had the New Year special meal... pork ribs and roasted chicken.. with lots of vegetables, n my favourite corn on cob... it's a platter for 2 pax.. pork ribs is so succulent, chicken grilled with Nepalese spices... üòãüòãüòã... enjoyable meal ... good food, good company.
Thanks Tom for this special menu ...
solid food. best ÂíïÂôúËÇâ anywhere honestly meat is tender batter is thin

System glitched and doubled order a dish for us, causing some awkwardness when the extra dish came.. üò®üò®

Steak was as so-so as I remembered‚Ä¶ not recommended for the price, though the fish and chips and chicken were ok.

Overall lighting was dark and made the place seem old and run-down, although it being old is very much true.

Btw, the pasta was some next level dry and weird. Don‚Äôt recommend to try unless you want to reminisce days during outfield when you‚Äôre eating the infamous pasta ration pack üò∞üò∞üò•üò∞
Relaxed atmosphere. Despite the full house, service was prompt and food arrived fairly quickly. Food was prepared well. The carpark valet service was a plus indeed.

Horrible service staffs.
After the 4th dish, there was an unexplained 1 hour interval. When the final 2 dishes and dessert arrived, the table was a mess. After I took some noodle, the service staff asked if they can clear the table then they just proceed.
The food was below average. Suckling was dried and hard.

The only thing acceptable was the red bean pan cake. Not too sweet.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: A very solid 3. Had their signature set K. But I think my chicken was alittle over-charred and there was a burnt taste to it. Even if I take that out of account, I felt the Nasi (rice) could be better and more fragrant. It's alittle starchy. The peanut to ikan ratio was also disappointing. But the chili is great. Overall if u happen to be here and have that Nasi Lemak or Indonesian BBQ craving, this would certainly satisfy u. But I think they can still improve. I will give it another try some time again. üëç

Probably a poor choice to come to a ramen place for salmon don

The salmon was fresh . Just a little weirded out by the warm rice that warmed my salmon . Everything was warm by the time it reached me . Warm raw fish isn't my thing .
Portions not the type to leave you satisfied . Felt like I was rationing myself during the meal . The fish looks so sparse on the rice like my hair on my head .
The gyoza, an offhand top up was probably the highlight of the meal .

If I ever returned,  it probably would be for ramen and not this , assuming I do . The only draw seems to be a place you bring friends if it needs to be halal .

Everything came to around $26 I feel I paid more for the deco than for my food
It's the kind of experience I'll say leaves you feeling shortchanged.
If I have to say it , 3 stars are entirely because of the deco and staff
Tasty food at reasonable prices. Do try the fried fish with mango sauce

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
Value for money.

Sometimes have to wait longer due to a long crowd during peak period.

Portion might be small for more than average eater.

2nd visit here. First visit was good. But this time, not so.

Reached around 6.45pm and was told the wait will be 30 to 40 mins, which we are fine. After 40mins, one fried chicken was brought out and rice. With each dish coming out every 10mins, need 1 over hour for all dishes to be out at 8pm.

Food is good however it's taking too long for hungry diners.

P.s. Another table came later than us but got our their food earlier.

Went on Sunday around 3.30pm, got a table immediately without queuing.
Many more choices for food than the franchise HDB stall.
Food tastes good. Staff is helpful.
Many oders for delivery during our meal time.
This restaurant provides lunch promotion during weekdays. You may pay a visit.
Lovely meal but the branch is severely understaffed!! Management should amp up their hiring because the staff there are clearly doing their best, very dedicated and polite but struggling.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: It was unpleasent . Staff don‚Äôt know about their promotion and insist they are right . I think worst exprience so far will not go back again. Management called to explain but i had already dine in without any promotion . I hope when customer see this , be wary of the term and condition .

Was there at 12.30pm.While waiting for medical appointment.Ordered a rice,sotong & 2 veggies with begedel and 1 can of coke and was charged $9.00 in a bills.Don't know of it was the actaual or certainly the staff just made the priced.

Food smells very good when walking pass. Complimentary prawn crackers and Tom yum soup was good. Drinks were quite nice too. Ordered the butterfly pea lime soda and the Thai milk tea. The rest of the food were ok at best. Garlic pork belly and Poo Ja (shrimp and meat in crab shell)  was too peppery, Crab meat fried rice was bland and did not have wok hey. Not worth the price.

Had lunch here at ichiban sushi (AMK) and we have a nice time, quick service and good food and drinks...tendon set is nice and the cook on the egg still runny even it was fried with tempura batter is tricky, rice that comes together with tendon is white and fluffy, unagi terrayaki sushi is nice together with the fried gyoza..had my fave appetizer of Japanese tofu and finished it off with yuzu orange drink which is just refreshing...why did I gave 3 stars? It is my 1st visit maybe next time it will be more than 3‚≠ê...all in all, one can try this place....

Very hard to find coffee shop nestled under the HDB blocks. The ramen was prepared very quickly and it‚Äôs definitely value for money. I tried the all ingredients ramen bowl and the ramen was cooked al dente and the broth was really flavorful. Definitely worth a try! I would have given it a 4 stars if the coffee shop was in better shape.

Food portion was kinda big for us. My parents, hubby and I sharing 2 noodles (hor fun & meesua), 2 veg, and 1 fish soup for dinner.. very filling. Prices are reasonable. Food taste good! Staff are friendly. Little walking from Novena Square. Will be closed for renovation 10-21 Sep 2018.
Friendly, good services, nice food and nice environment. üëçüèª

Nice nasi ambeng. Tastes as if home-cooked. Good portion for 2. Price is ok for me.
Will come back if I‚Äôm in the areaüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

Fashioned after a tea house, this restaurant serves dim sum and Chinese dishes. A
Good variety of dim sum available but I think there are better dim sum out there. The best dish were the white bait fish in truffle oil and roast pork noodles. Congee was disappointing as it was bland. Spinach with 3 eggs lacked flavour. Pork ribs had more yam than meat! Egg tarts are bite sized, flaky and warm. We had booth seats which can sit 4-5 people comfortably. The dishes are served using the smart train belt which is quite efficient but not easy for children to handle.
Service was fast and attentive. Overall, a pleasant experience however the food quality not as good as expected.
We love this restaurant - the food quality, taste and service are well worth a visit.
Glad to hv found this cool hangout spot. Good food. Friendly staff.

waited for almost 40mins for my meal to be served correctly, my family ate finish already then i can start eating‚Ä¶i ordered lobster with rice but at first they served me seafood spaghetti then followed by lobster with spaghetti??2 wrong orders served consecutively, manager wasn‚Äôt sincere and apologetic too , and lastly the rice was hard.., lobster was cold
Excellent Thai food. The pictures says it all. Great service

Was worried after seeing their recent reviews on Google but was very satisfied after ordering 2 times,

Taste : 9/10
Appearance : 10/10

One of the best Japanese delivery on grabüí™
New Japanese food stall tucked in a corner of coffeeshop. Their food is nice. Average $8 to $9 per person. You can choose two sides and either rice or noodles to go along with the food.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content:
I m very disappointed and disgusted with the service all the frontline today. My order was for 8 thosai n 6 vadais. They took about an hour that after i approached them after numerous attempts. They just totally ignored my order. And when they did my packing i realised actually the thosais were prepared long way back. And after an hour i asked the staff whether the vadais were done, she didnt have the decency to admit that they are still making it Instead she said she is packing it.
I would never logo there again n for extra sambar they charged me $6,fter i spent $47.
They don have the respect for timing. And i feel sorry that the food delivery guys had to endure the same as me. I sincerely feel the management shd look seriously into this. The staff is rude, unapproachable and just have a sickening attitude.
bad service, long waiting time for food. leave customers unattended. those who came later was being served first.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
-The food was fresh, and atmosphere was nice after dark. Handmade red chili, garlic sauce was excellent, in harmony with every other food.
-The staffs were not so kind. Long queue but you can make reservation. They have a time limit of 90minutes eating.
>>It‚Äôs located in hawker center where you can enjoy your saturday night at one place. How about eating Mookata as the first round and then moving to Tiger beer stall that is close to by for the second round?üòÇ

Super unfriendly, only want exact amount. If need change he won't let you buy and basically forces u to get extra dishes so he doesn't have to give you change. Lastly it's only so-so never understood why there's always a queue there anyway
By far one of the best mala I‚Äôve ever had. The crispy potatoes are to die for and the drinks are a perfect pairing for the spicy meal.
My daughters and I enjoyed the breakfast selection which are suitable for Sunday morning brunch. The service was quick and friendly. Peggy was particularly helpful üëç

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
The jajangmyun compared to the other korean noodle shops is a lot more wet and less greasy. A good balance of sweet and savory, with a handful of onions and pork belly cubes. Noodles were chewy and didn't have an alkaline smell.

Tangsuyok ordered for Small is more than enough for 2 pax. They are in bite sized chunks instead of long streaks which was easier to eat. Batter is crispy and not too thick.

Texture of chives pancake was thin and lightly crispy. It is easily torn with chopsticks and still has a chewy stretchy texture. Can imagine eating this with alcohol as an accompaniment.

Condiments such as kimchi, yellow radish, onion bits and szechuan veggie were given in small portions.üëç And water is complimentary. Ambience was very much like an atas korean-Chinese restaurant :)

Total bill came up to be ~$72 and would say its towards the high side.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Thank you B1 personal staff to attend to my dad‚Äôs guests this evening. Your service is excellent! Even though we had numerous requests, you did not falter and accommodated to our requests; even taking initiative to cut the cake after the celebration. Thanks for being part of this good memory of my dad‚Äôs 70th birthday. Sorry I did not manage to get your name. Kudos to all the staff who were helping in one way or another, even though the place was full, you all were polite and approachable. Food was great, everyone loved it. Even the vegetarian food was done very well. Thank you!

We ordered the Claypot Rice, curry fish head, dai luk Noodle, San lou Noodle, and salted egg bitter gourd. The Claypot Rice was really nothing impressive. There have been other Claypot Rice which are much better than this place. Especially for the price tag, totally not worth it.

However, the other dishes were very good. San lou Noodle and dai luk Noodle was good. Curry fish head was also spicy and also filling.

That being said, the very off putting thing about this place is that after you order, before you eat, you have to pay up. I did not mind the first time before starting to eat, but during our meals, when we ordered additional drinks, it was really off putting and a hassle.

Will recommend this place if your coming here for the zhi char, but definitely not for the Claypot Rice.

This is a very nice 4.5 star lunch spot for some cozy family style non-pretentious Shanghainese fare. The popular dish seemed to be the Shanghai fried buns, but although the meat and soup inside was flavorful, I find the dough a little too soft - had better versions of this elsewhere. The star of the show was surprisingly the fried egg with yellow chives. It doesn't look like much, but the egg was fluffy with many layers, full of umami and the earthiness of the yellow chives just gave it that perfect bite. The other surprise was the stir fried french beans - not oily at all, each bite juicy with a spicy kick. The chicken noodles were springy and nice, and the xiao long baos were okay. Would be back to taste the rest of the dishes. Packed on a wednesday afternoon for lunch. Note, they only accept cash - and call to reserve in advance.
Went around lunchtime on weekday. The queue is long, waiting time about 30min. Ordered the chicken teriyaki bento set. The chicken teriyaki is nice. Priced at 4.50.
Very affordable western place, only downside is the location at quite an isolated place.
Horrible food.. So much expensive and worst still rude staff

Been coming to this place for more than 9 years and clocked more than 700 visits.
The original staff and cashier are no longer here, but the taste of the food is still up to standard, unlike other branches where it can be inconsistent.
Only small issue of teh tarik ICED tastes too diluted. Recommend to drink hot beverages if you can help it.
I will personally recommend the sugar and milk paper prata, egg prata and sambal chicken.
If you like floss, then can go for their umami prata and other specialty pratas like the sg50 prata.
Now very convenient to come here since springleaf mrt station is just 2 mins walk.
Food is really nice especially their famous claypot spring chicken with cabbage! Service was awesome! Really good place to bring your family here!

It has been a while since I've had salted egg anything, so my review may be a little biased. The salted egg pork ribs were flavourful and the sauce was generous. Enough salted egg omph in my opinion. The oysters in the oyster omelette were big and tasted fresh - no fishy taste. French beans were meh for the price paid and could be skipped. The special tofu didn't feel very special but still alright. The fried Ee mian was not bad too. Total cost for 5 dishes was $50 for 4 pax.
This is second times I went there having dinner with my family members. Foods are nice n delicious. Staffs very polite n good service.

Taste - beats the Chinese food in Kopitiam nearby
Price - a bit expensive for the portion and location.

I left 30 mins after finishing my cold dishes - as the hot dishes are still in the kitchen - not a place to be if you are just here when hungry.
Okay, like any other Genki sushi restaurant in the chain.  It's not too bad although sushiro is slightly better with respect to their offerings.  The queue is long but they try hard.

Love their food. Their hotpot is good and their chi zhar is good. They're one of our favourite stalls at Jalan Kayu, but unfortunately the restaurant is severely understaffed. There's only one poor guy as waiter during peak hours, and you can see him struggling to juggle so many tables.

If you're the owner of the place who happe  to read this, please for the love of good food hire more help for your restaurant.
Food is tasty as it not salty,  seasoning well balance.. üëçüí∞ Value for money.. Try yourself
Always good. Value, clean tasting lunches. Chicken burrito bowl ftw

Ordered mushroom sauce rib eye steak. Ordered medium but was unevenly cooked. Otherwise no complains, was a good plate of steak with nice amount of sides. If u want fuss free quality western food this is worth a consideration.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Food is higher priced than its competitors. But they make the yummiest xiao long bao. I wish they have more menu cos the food choices are quite limited.

I've walked past this cafe several times but this was my first time actually dining in. We were pleasantly surprised by the sheer variety offered. The food was also reasonably priced and the portions were generous.

I had the BBQ chicken with baked potato and fries. I loved how juicy the chicken was. The fries were crisp on the outside and soft on the inside, yum!
Went today, not much crowd during sunday lunch time. Friendly aunty. We ordered chee chong fun, siew mai, ha gao. Quite standard. Dont try the red bean bun, super dry. Rest of the food was ok.
Yummilicious noodle which taste really like Msia.  Worth queuing and seller is so friendly.
Good food. Value for money. Nice seating for an open air coffee shop.
Best prata ever tasted

Lots of delicious food.

Fried carrot cake is ok.
Lontong is great.
Chilli Ban Mian deproved.

Penang Char Kway Teow($4.50)üòã
Kway Teow were cooked using pork lard oil to cook as I had some crunchy pork lard bits while eating. Big portion of eggs and bean sprout used. With few sauce & seasoning, the aromatic tastisfying Kway Teow with a mild spicy kick served with 2 big fresh deshell tender prawn is ready to be eaten.
Always buy but quite ex. Even add more sauce ask for 80c. Haha
Amongst all the parta and thosai are very ordinary with very less oil
All food and beverages are tasty. However to improve on table cleanliness

Food was alright and portions are huge. Price reasonable since the portions are so huge. Not so sure why mothers day quite a lot of food on the menu are not available. There was no peking duck, no dimsum etc. You can make reservations.

its very bad. we waited for like 2hours just to get these tiny small bowls of noodles and rice worth like 5bucks. i mean it iS a sushi restaurant but like the waiting time was solong?!?! at first we entered we wanted buy rice and noodles but they were SOLD OUT. so we waited. LIEK AROUND AN HOUR. then finally after we ordered.. we waited AROUND WNOTHER HOUR. (might be highly exaggerated, but basically we arrived around 1130am then we left around 1pm+)  then the food come so less one ): right now we ate at mac donalds bcs our stomachs arent fullüòî

but the staff are attentive and served us well, its just the kitchens kinda slow. and i guess when u go to a sushi place, just get sushiüëç btw, food is kinda ehh average.

The clams soup and yam are so yummy. We queried why the clams soup did not come with vegetables as stated in the menu, the chef and manager came over to verify and gave us a new bowl... Very caring and conscientious.

Ate at this restaurant for the first time today and we were impressed by its taste and service! Loved the garlic naan which was a little crispy on the outside and sag mutton which was so tender. Lady boss was also nice to help us inform the kitchen to remove the spice in the mutton dish and came over to check that it was done so when we were eating. Will definitely be back!

Place is not the most convenient in Singapore but the restaurant is rather quiet, good for people who want a quieter environment. Servers are friendly and helpful. Ordered chicken quesadilla, beef fajita and braised beef cheeks. Portions are above average sized. Beef cheeks were soft and flavorful. Quesadilla was not overly cheesy. Fajita was average. Guacamole texture and consistency could be better.
One of the best mee rebus I‚Äôve ever had. If not for the above average spiciness, I‚Äôd have another plate for sure. Be sure to add on a fried chicken wing for good measure!

(Translated by Google) Indonesian Malay style Western food The menu has been changing. The food in each store is different except for the pumpkin soup. The recent salmon with sauce is good, not too many people, fast and good choices

Another excellent meal here.
Service is efficient and friendly.
Reasonably priced.

Just had a couple side dishes here. The gyoza super nice, just the right amount of crispness. They are homemade according to the shop worker. The stir-fried mushrooms, wow. They got a little smoky flavor from the grill and if you're a mushroom lover you'll definitely want to get this. I don't even like onions but I ate all the onions in this too because they were cooked well and the sauce was very flavorful.
Lovely chicken and Beef, and the rasam is amazing
Cheap & Great Western Fix

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content:
Hosting a company dinner on a very wet Friday evening. The staff was very helpful. Got some umbrellas out for us and was patience with our demands. Everything we ordered was delicious!
Will definitely be back :)
Steak is good for their price range but sides can improve standard.

Great prices and excellent quality of food. The truffle beef don was spectacular and the crispy egg yolk fish skin and aburi salmon sushi was also great. I would definitely be back and recommend it to my friends
Chicken is above average but the fried eggplant in mushroom sauce is good. Service is excellent, they refill our tea and ice promptly.
The food is good especially the commando.. Advanced reservation is essential as the places gets crowded quick..

Worth the try! I‚Äôm not picky about food so it‚Äôs decent for me! Tho my bf who ate the sashimi said it‚Äôs not super fresh but still okay:) Love the fried salmon skin & egg mentaiko!! Rice bowl with the fried chicken was nice too~ But can get gelak over time, portion was good (for me cos i‚Äôm a small eater) Big fried ebi prawn also one of my fav ü§§

Food came fairly fast, staff was friendly & polite! Though had to wait alil at the entrance, im guessing cos they had 2 staff working (1 clearing table 1 at cashier) while others are on break or smth? So be more understanding towards them! Will come back :)

Also for every $20 spent u can get coins to play a catcher / kiap kiap for an ice cream outside their store!! and my bf did managed to catch one hahaha

For a place describing its specialty as clean eating, it was a massive disappointment. All three dishes we had were dark, spicy and heavy tasting. The interiors are pretentiously dark and service standards are straight out of a neighbourhood zhi char coffee shop.
Simply, don‚Äôt bother...

Delicious food and the portion is generous. The fried prawn tasted fresh and well crisped and that‚Äôs  a  clear testimonial of the good cooking skill.   The rest of the seafood in our Tom Yum soup were fresh too. Well visit again!

It‚Äôs a decent mee siam
Cost SGD 3 for this
A little bit spicy (even without adding the chilli)

Great value and quality western cuisine. We liked their ribeye steak, pork chops and bacon spaghetti. Can skip the bananas shake though. For those who prefer beer, they serve good beer at reasonable prices, all without the 10% service charges.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The latte which looks like long kept lemon tea. And the char grill chicken, is over burnt chicken. The standard really drop a lot. Beside the steak and fish. Please to order the char grilled here.

Poor service
Great food though

Nice homely Japanese eatery here! The katsu don is quite nice and unique with the addition of mushrooms. The salmon is ok, ebi tempera and karaage is good. The grilled squid is also fresh and bouncy! Like and check in to their fb to get a free wakami, it‚Äôs delicious! The roasted barley tea is also aromatic!

Use the kiap to take the rojak, there is the typical fried potato, fried square beancurb, hotdog which are fried, fried fillet fish, flour items which are fried, contains some fried egg or vegetable. There is fried prawn on a fried flour or just mass fried small prawn on flour. There is also fried sotong available. Once you have chosen the items, they will refry it to perfection. Comes with cucumber

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: The dishes were excellent - the cold crab, braised duck with bean curd (which was boneless), conpoy braised with eight vegetarian treasures, and yam paste with pumpkin and gingko nuts (seems to use pandan syrup instead of lard). The oyster omelette was good.

Brought my 3 year old and 1 year old to your Novena Square outlet last night. As they are extremely fussy eaters we brought food we knew they would eat but we were told ‚Äúno outside food allowed‚Äù. Your waitress had just served 2 plates of rice for them whilst I was preparing to order dinner for my wife and I then she noticed the food we brought for our kids, proceeded to reject my explanation that it was for our fussy eating kids, and promptly removed the kid‚Äôs rice from the table. It was 7pm prime dinner time but you only had 2 other occupied tables of customers in the whole restaurant yet your waitress still saw fit to prevent our kids from eating knowing this would cause us to leave because she can‚Äôt even make a no outside food policy exception for a toddler and an infant. Way to go Curry Times, way to go. So much for touting yourselves as a ‚Äúkids friendly‚Äù family restaurant. üëéüèªüëéüèªüëéüèª

Fun dining experience. The dim sum comes on the train and my 2 year old loved it. Service was good and staff were friendly and polite which, if I may say, is uncommon in such casual dining places in Singapore. The food was good but a bit too salty for me.

Came to know thru a friend by word and visited them. Finally, managed to get the real taste of home-cooked food with a lot of varieties and a very reasonable price. Very clean and friendly as well. I Will visit often.
Nice food. Dun forget to try their red rubby dessert..  Authentic thai food. Reasonable price too.. the staff is really attentive. Recommended to try it..
Ordered ribeye, tasted like black pepper chicken breast. Never coming back.

Perfect place for a decent chicken rice. Ambience is great, service staff is polite. Price is at the high side, but still worth it. The vegetable is lightly salted and chicken rice is very fragrance. Their signature chicken is still the best as compared to the roast chicken. Chilli and ginger paste taste fresh and great too. Will come back again.
Food nice n cheap

Very nice and typical Thai food.  I have been here many times and still always my first choice whenever I craving for Thai cuisine.
Its not only nice food,  very cheap some more.  No GST,  no service charge.
Where to find?

My favourite Thai food. Found it a month ago and I think has been eating there at least 3x a week! Loved the steamed fish with lime, basil minced chicken rice, tom yam, seafood tanghoon, green curry chicken, tanghoon salad... go try!

Underrated gem, my experience having a meal there not too long ago has been a pleasant one.

Food variety is good, and those i ordered were really tasty and had good portions. We had the seafood fried rice, spinach, lychee sweet and sour pork, and the xiao long bao, all of which i found were really good and i don't really have any criticism for any of them; all were freshly made to order and not overcooked. Special mention to the sweet and sour pork which was crispy on the outside and juicy pipping hot on the inside coated with the sweetness from the lychee and tomato-based sauce fused in one.

The service was also impeccable; the staffs there were so attentive and most of all polite. They were welcoming and quick to ensure we had a really pleasant dining experience by tending to our requests or query (on dishes) very promptly.

Really recommend for people, especially people around the neighbourhood to come by here and show them some support.

I myself will definitely consider to come by here more often for meals after having experience how good the food and service here is.

One of the better Tim Sum place in SengKang
Tim Sum quality is consistently good.
Avoid lunch and dinner times during weekends due to overcrowding.
Drink portions are small
Service has room for improvement
Reliable consistent local curry and biryani fare served in generous portions - will never be disappointed

Food tastes good. Price is cheap. This is a small family restaurant with 3 persons only. That might be why some people reviewed abt service. Coz they don‚Äôt have a lot manpower. But they also don‚Äôt charge 19%.  And the auntie boss is friendly.  So in general worth revisiting.
Expected price for good quality pork and beef don but still on the pricier side. Quick and efficient service, friendly staff
Affordable price, taste of the food Is what you can expect from the price
It‚Äôs always our family‚Äôs all time favourite restaurant! Staffs are friendly and attentive!

Good dim sum place in the mature Toa Payoh housing estate. Location is so accessible.  There is also a lift, albeit a very basic and simple model for those who need assistance.  Just give a call to the number for assistance.
Glad that the management is able to pull through the Covid period.  Saw many families, old & young.

(Translated by Google) The taste is good but the quantity is low compared to the price.

Great place to enjoy Western food. Nice and cozy environment.

Located opp Sembawang S.C.
Shophouse unit and no aircon. Fans sufficient to keep the area cool.
Claypot rice was piping hot and flavourful.
Homemade cripsy beancurd really cripsy on skin and very tasty!
Chilli and dark sauce given on the side in bottles.
Recommended! üëç

First time here, Ordered their signature curry chicken and I would have preferred if their curry was slightly more spicy. My friend and I dropped by at 6:30 and the curry served was lukewarm at best so that could be why it didn't taste as good but I would definitely revisit to try more of their other dishes!

You know this feeling... when everything just went your way. Popped by for dinner with family after the ST article's  and boy, we truly enjoyed ourselves. Ordered the signatures and EVERY SINGLE DISH HIT THE SPOT for us. The outstanding ones are the sotong and lady finger chincalok, poached pork, KL dai lok mee paired with the oh so good and spicy sambal and the other ni. Ingredients are fresh, and the taste is natural just nicely balanced by the sauces and spices, without being overly salty, or sweet. Service is also impeccable, spacious and ambience makes for a fun evening dinner with good conversations.  Will definitely return to try the other dishes.

If you are craving push cart dimsum this is one of the few places that serves it, they start 8am.

Food quality is average The skin of har gow is so so n thick .  Seafood Bamboo roll was nice .  But found the char siew Chee Cheong fun to have porky smell .

Below expectations. Food was very oily and portion was little. Sausage Aglio - 5/10, oily, salty, unimpressive.

Creamy chicken pasta - extremely creamy, overwhelming, bad @ 2/10.

Price - your usual neighbourhood caf√© price but high for food quality

Caf√© was noisy, not for chilling  people!
The lamian is good but taste could have been better

Came here on a weekday afternoon for lunch upon a friend's recommendation. We arrived at about 12nn to find the restaurant packed with customers! Thankfully we had made reservations. A nice comfortable setting where you can have a relaxing lunch with friends and/or family. Staff are not quite so attentive though and they seem to be short-handed. Food took a while to arrive, maybe also because of the crowd.
For 3 pax, we ordered a Grilled Fish in Sichuan Mala broth, a serving of mixed vegetables and a serving of Mala Crystal Bao. Portions were just right for us. I did not quite fancy the Mala broth - it was not spicy enough. Though the friends liked it, where one commented that the "fish" was done almost like a real fish. Hmm.. I am not a fan of plant-based meat.
While we had 2 dishes that claimed to be Mala, I did not think there was sufficient spice at all to be classified as... Mala??
Nevertheless, the environment was nice and made for a good choice to have a catch-up meal with friends.
Conveniently located on L2 of Royal Square @Novena.
Long queues during peak hours, but very efficient service. Standard McDonald's menu available.

Very reasonably priced. Quite a lot of variety such as mee rebus , lontong and mee siam but they get sold out before lunchtime. Very friendly and helpful proprietors. Sometimes they have cockle or kerang sambal which is hard to find . Their sambals are not too spicy and very tasty. Lontong sayur is kept hot unlike other places
bad service and taste. just near to my workplace.

Looks nice from the outside and the restaurant is full of people. We had high expectations when we went in, however we were rather disappointed with the food quality.

Xiao long Bao was not hot, just slightly warm.. seems like it has been pre cooked and left in the kitchen for quite sometime.. skin is thick and the pork just tastes weird.
Love the place; very bright, without the +10% and stuff. Definitely an excellent place to hang out for supper.
Portion is good and ingredients are very fresh!!

Huge menu, very friendly service staffs and owners and lots of wine tasting events.

Food is good and experimental. Overall, a very friendly place.

Wonderful Hokkien dishes that include the Xing Hua Bee Hoon, Cabbage Fried Rice and Toufu. Oh yes, the teas are refillable with hot water.
It‚Äôs a nice, comfy place right next to Fernvale LRT and I would come back again with my family.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Enjoyed a casual lunch here after running errands in the Toa Payoh neighbourhood. We almost always order the same favourites whenever we dine here: crispy bait Wuxi-style, dan dan noodles, xiao long bao & mala spiced dumplings. Yums, never fail to satisfy.
Delicious food and we loved the fish soup which was light, slightly sweet and tasty. Will order from them again for sure.
Better off eating the food court upstairs or macs. Worst quality of service imaginable
Tried my first podi thosai here. Super delicious! Also had the curry fish which was scrumptious! Wait staff were friendly too. Will be coming back!

I don't usually give review. But this restaurant for the price and service really need improvement.  Service was bad, seems like understaff and we had to wait very long before the staff has time to attend to us. Food was so so only, nothing amazing. The duck to me was not very fresh, got a strong frozen duck smell. The rest of the dishes was ok. Considering the service, and food quality, this will be our first and last visit.
If you go at peak hours be ready to wait for an hour for your food and when it arrives it might not even be what you ordered. They clearly need to hire more staff.
Nice biryani. Friendly services.
Britney is a cheerful staff and she has a wonderful memory. She got all our orders correct even without writing them down. Fast on her feet and courteous.

Highly recommend for Iberico Hoho Don. Meat is so tender,  juicy and smoky. The taste and texture is so good! Make me want to come back to eat again! The staff is friendly and  good service. I think they should hire more staff. Always crowded and busy
Service crew was good, the food was so-so but could pass. Ordered a sirloin steak and a chicken steak. We ordered one set too. Overall it is a nice place, not too crowded.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
Dinner was open 6-9 for this restaurant. We came in at 6pm for their buffet and orders were sent at 6.10. waited till 7.45pm for our food not to be served yet. There was a table beside that made a scene for their food not served and they got theirs served when they were clearly at least 30min later than us to arrive. Did not want to cause a scene and left after paying for what we ordered based on ala-carte pricing.

Clearly a NEVER come again. Unless you have a great patience to wait 2hrs for your food to arrive when having a buffet. It was just a pure terrible experience
Good, tasty and affordable food on order..

Ok the photo may look a bit messy but this mee rebus is good stuff. Noodles portion is larger than average, n the $5 'Power' version also gets u a decent chunk of chicken. Gravy remains nice n thick to the very last strand of noodle
as a non mala eater this place CONVERTED me took me through heaven and hell (from the HOTness) and back down as a loyal worshipper üôèüèºüôèüèºüôèüèº

I don't stay in this neighborhood but previously I saw constant crowds streaming in so I wanted to try it myself.
But probably due to the fact that it's CNY day 3, most of the items were sold out. Even the chili for the Penang Char Kway Teow was sold out and I had this blend CKT, goes with their signature fried fermented bean curd pork, which doesn't have enough of the fermented bean curd taste and most of the portion was fats instead of meat. Chendol lacks of Gula melaka taste, good for those who don't want their dessert to be sweet.
And one and off you will get shouting from the kitchen staff (and a full 7 letter vulgarity for the CNY day 03)
Overall it was a disappointed meal and I can't get why people will still patronise them. Never again for me.
Best Indian Rojak I ever tried. Clean food in clean place. Must try at Yishun Chong Pang!!

Have tried all TMC/TFC outlets. But Winstedt outlet, countless times‚Ä¶but first time review üòÇ.

23 Oct, 345pm

Food: Delicious CONSISTENTLY. Never disappoint me every time. Portion of food is alot, and they gave complimentary plate of wings.

Atmosphere: Nice ambience and cosy feeling. Great for couples dating or want some quiet meals together.

Customer service: As usual lead by 1 superb supervisor ADY together with JESTER and AMAN, they‚Äôre friendly and helpful as always. Although they are busy with wedding prep event which starts at 5pm, they still put the EFFORT to ask patrons if food was alright and if we need anything etcs üëçüèºüëçüèºüëçüèº. Bottomline is, GREAT CUSTOMER SERVICE.

Yes its a little bit pricey, BUT for the quality of food, food portion, service rendered etcs will justified the price. They do give vouchers too. If you are lucky, at times they will give away cakes, its sooooo delicious ü§§. Today i bought their durian pengat cake, A MUST TRY.

And since we‚Äôre here for my wife and mine belated birthday, TMC gave 2 complimentary cakes and ice cream scoops!! Isn‚Äôt that GENEROUS??

May TMC prosper and grow even more in years to come. ü§≤üèª
Cheap and Nice

This is the second time they forgot items for my takeway food...first was the extra saambar and today was the bru coffee...
Hello management..make sure your staff packs all the items not miss out...we cant be going to the restaurant to collect ...
Ordered takeaway ebi tempura udon and I went home without the ebi packed in. Had to make a trip back to the restaurant after I had reached home. Lapse of service!
Nice and relax place. Food are delicious üòã. Important Aircon is Power ..
Cheap but delicious, $1 dollar nasi lemak is fantastic not only in price but taste as well

I got Biryani rice with mutton last night from this restaurant.
Its tasty but bit disappointed with more quantity of potato than mutton pieces in the dish.

proper tonkatsu at a decent price , what's more to ask ?

paired with great beer , and a fun environment, will come more often!

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Standard dropped a lot since the last time I visited. Ordered chicken cutlet and felt the meat tasted slightly weird. The inside was alittle pinkish. Informed the manager and he told me their chicken is supposed to be slightly pinkish on the inside due to the marinate they use. Gave him the benefit of a doubt and continued with my meal.

#SeriMuslimFood is definitely one of the better Malay food stalls in this area. A long queue is expected but thankfully waiting time is not very long as they have many people taking and preparing your order.
.
My favourite items from their menu are #MeeRebus and #Lontong. Standard menu items ranges from SGD$2.50 to SGD$3.00.
.
#StanzFoodHunts #TamanJurongShoppingCentre #MuslimCuisine
Great Sichuan food, affordable prices, and good service

Very nicely battered Fish & Chips.
A better deal if you are a student, they offer half price for students for some of their dishes for lunch
A western food gem in AMK! The mushroom brown sauce was really good and we love the curly fries! There is an ongoing Shopee promotion where you can get $2 off every payment transaction!
awesome food awesome price awesome service. just need to wait a little while during peak hour
Good place to chill. Nice ambience. The usual halal Indian food.

Was recommended to come here and the place didn't disappoint! Really surprised at the food quality and taste despite being located in an obscure location of a residential neighbourhood. The residents in the area really lucked out!

Food and good and tasty, also generally not too spicy. Service was good but the food took a little longer than expected to come out. From the looks of things, the kitchen is pretty small so can't be helped. Totally forgot to take a pic of their winner dish cause it was so good. Some special pork which you stuff into a fried mantou. Sorry this doesn't help much.

Definitely will be back to eat again.

Fresh ingredients, healthy options and delicious. It‚Äôs always crowded during peak hours, the name is apt. Add on options are available apart from the main dishes and it‚Äôs a welcome change to the regular food options in NTU.

Did lunch today, was dissapointed to learn no actual BL available, however that was made up with the flavor of homestyle cooking. Had a generous bowl of yogurt and the Ice morru was 2 persons share. IF owner reading always room for improvement.

Excellent service provided by Alice from Compassone. She was extremely friendly and helpful. I saw her paying attention to the customers and took initiative to offer help. Very hardworking elderly lady. Other staff not as helpful, cashier was a little grumpy. Food is excellent as usual.
Breaded Fish with Pork Chop gives good value for money.
The prata is very crispy and nice. The aunty tending the cashier is also friendly and helpful.

Order for delivery through Grab. Msg the driver to make sure that they have give me the correct item which was mutton poori set. They rider reply inform the staff told him all correct is mutton they give. When I receive my order they give me chicken instead of mutton. Why they want to lie to the rider? Dun tell me they dun know what is mutton what is chicken how they look like?
Best Thai food in Singapore and it's not even close. Been a customer for over a decade (when they were at Siglap and Funan). The staff are super as well.
Worst burger my brother has ever eaten; stuffed with wedges. Pan fried mushroom was bitter, wedges was still a bit raw, black pepper sauce was terribly salty and chicken chop was burnt.

Good chicken rice Service was good!
But chopping Chef and Trsinee....must clear once the plastic bin is half full og nones....looks aweful and unhygienic.....DO Not  wait till its so full that customers csn see....when we are looking at them chopping.....very unpro??
Very quiet, no crowd. Good place to have a simple breakfast and chit chat with friends.
Excellent variety of home cooked vegetables and friendly staff..Food Taste authentic good and place is a hidden gem.

On 23rd April, 2021 11.50 am, just suffered a very very rude service from the cashier. idk the name of him
He told me to got out of here and did not have meal here, just because he did not see my checkin????? Actually I had shown him several times.
Very mean and rude!
Placed order via Deliveroo for delivery from 6.45 - 7.15 pm. Waited for ONE HOUR until 7.45 pm to be told order cancelled. One star already too many.

(Translated by Google) Food portions are big and taste good. The price is reasonable, and the discounts of eatigo or their own are very attractive.
Food portions are big and taste good. The price is reasonable, and the discounts of eatigo or their own are very attractive.

Food portions are big and taste good.  The price is reasonable, and the discounts of eatigo or their own are very attractive.

great food selection and great ambience. The staff and service are all nice as well. Recommended if you would like to at with your lrents or family as it has wide range food selection.

Wanton Mee. Nice Roast Duck. HK style with Honey Roasted Char Siew. Comparable to Kay Lee Roast.

Lots of takeaways. Try their Chinatown Claypot Chicken... Authentic.

Went here my father-in-law's birthday party and asked for a mango mousse but they ran out of stock.

Gladly they're offering an onde-onde cake as a replacement despite the price is more expensive.

Nice cozy restaurant in the hood. Great for dining out with friends. Food is top quality and service is great. Price is reasonable too.
Affordable price with fresh sashimi. Food is nice and place are clean and tidy.

Uncommon to find this type of fish soup in Singapore. It contained the type of salty flavour that should be from dried white amur (i guess). The fish they use in their fish soup is the typical spanish mackerel (batang).

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Horrible service, especially the chinese auntie, took my order and missed out a few items. Told the chinese auntie and missed item didn't come and had to prompt again. Bill didn't tally with my order, with extra items charged in it which I believe the auntie thought I was ordering more items instead of the item being missed out on their end? Ice cream is not free flow either. Definitely not coming back, unpleasant experience.

Pardon me. I usually take photos of food after I have tasted them. We only ordered the claypot rice and a coffee.
Claypot is average as I had tasted better than this in Bukit Batok East Ave 3. As for this one, rice and salted fish pass my standard. Will not specifically drive down for this but can drop by when I‚Äôm near to this area. Potion is slightly lesser but I like the potion of vegetables provided. Oh yes, chicken texture and cut taste and look funny. Maybe is due to frozen chicken.
Next to the north point shopping mall. Breakfast and Lunch are good.

(Translated by Google) A whole chicken wrapped in cabbage and simmered in a clay pot is a favorite dish that cannot be tasted anywhere else. San Barsoton is also spicy and delicious.

(Original)
