I think food here, it‚Äôs authentic enough by Shanghainese standards. The fried bun taste really as good as anywhere you can find in Singapore.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Quite pricey for the small portion. Chili sauce is acceptable.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Very nice clean restaurant for meals with friends during this covid period. Driving there will be preferred as you will need to walk of you want to take public transportation. If you like teochew dishes then it's a recommended place for it.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Food is good. Ambience is good. Prices reasonable.

Tried it due to the many newspaper cuttings adorning stall front. 1 bergedil, 1 pineapple vege & 1 beef rendang for $7 is shockingly expensive. Definitely NOT the best rendang I've tried. Not worth coming back for even if passing by.

Came here with a booking at 530pm on a weekday. Still possible to walk-in, as most of the bookings were at 7pm. Service was good, staff was able to give suggestions and took care to make sure you are comfortable. Quality of food is there. The soup is nice. The sambal cod fish a little overdone to my taste. Do not have any fav dish although they all all good. The best for my companion is the dry laska.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: What I like about Tian Yuan Xiang Original Chicken Essence is that it is very easy to prepare, and tastes so good! Not smelly at all!

My expectations are high because of the reviews and is unfortunately unmet. Though it is not that bad but it's hype around here are not all that.

The Tom Yam is unlike other thai restos that are all just chili. The broth is tasty and rich. Overall, it's s ok. I'll give a higher score for the Beef Kailan due to its serving size and taste.
Friendly staff, Great food Great drinks!. However i think location wise can be improved as its very hot n humid there
Food doesn't taste great like before.  Standard drop abit.
The Kueh Teaw soup is not so tasty. The asam laksa is lack of sardin. However the Thai style fried tofu is good enough. The service is not bad though. Hope they can improve the food quality.

Was here on 22-May-2022 dinner and order 5 dishes. The famous claypot chickens rice was smooth and good. Other 3 dishes was alright. But the worst is the cereal prawn which cereal taste was ok but the prawn seem to either have 2 different species 1 of them look fresh healthy and the rest of the prawn was in dark black along edge of shell all over. Call for advise they said the rest in black is over oil flies and only 1 is just flies right. That‚Äôs the explain and place back the same dish on the table. Omg. Is that a good explanation and acceptable for dinner? That‚Äôs is totally and chef skill issue and was treated in these manner. Very disappointed indeed
Several trips her, must try Mash potatos,  rib eye steak and braised lamb. Corn is also quite nice for me.
I just feel I can get more food per dollar spent at other bbq joints. I wasn‚Äôt even full after eating the 200g beef set.

Reno is a bit old but basic cleanliness is acceptable.
Food is quite nice & prata is more of a crispy texture.
The curries are quite salty to personal liking...

Stumbled upon this non air-con Teochew restaurant. I like Teochew cuisine so why not. Ordered 3 simple dishes for lunch and they turned out good.
The standard of its Teochew braised duck, ÊΩÆÂ∑ûÂç§Ê∞¥È∏≠, is good enough to convince me to return again to try the other traditional Teochew dishes this restaurant has to offer.
It is reasonably priced too.
Only thing is.... No air-con üòÖ

Food was average. 4 of us had their steaks..all i have to say is you better have  sharks teeth n jaw to chew that meat. Felt like i was fighting the animal while eating it. Even toigh meat can be prepared to be relatively soft. Simoly tgrowing a piece of meat on the frying pan does not make it a steak.. Just my oppinion. Service and ambionce was nice though.

Worse experience ever
Came ordered from app
Water sold out. Ask waitress for water that say reply there‚Äôs no water here. So I have to req ice a drink water from hot tap‚Ä¶
Order a can of coke. From the start after I finish my meal the coke just served
Sushi Rices was bad
Raw ingredients wasn‚Äôt fresh
Service was bad

Location is good!
Ambience is good!!
Menu is good!!!
Food is good!!!!
This is a nice place to experience the Indian cuisine, taste is good but there is a lot of room to improvement!!!!!

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: They say one of the best Chicken Rice place. Hummm. I expect high but the outcome is below par for great chicken rice. I am not saying bad which u can see I still give 4 star. Just they cannot be regarded as best chicken rice. Their chicken is good and food is nice. Really worth to come. However for best chicken, u need some good cooking method and the tender of chicken must be smooth rather than a bit rough. Otherwise other food was also good.

The waitress who looks like a senior staff doesn‚Äôt even know peppercorn vs black pepper. I am well versed in both English and Chinese so the menu clearly is understood by me. Plus I love to enjoy food.  But not here. Sure, she is rude but I waited to see if the food is any good.   That glutinous rice rolls are horribly salty, the rice is not even cooked at a good temperature and everything is just mashed up and salty.  Doesn‚Äôt even have the fresh taste.  The so called chicken dish is so normal. The rice is really not cooked well(a restaurant with messed up rice‚Ä¶.), they mess up the order, comes over to do a so called I am sorry the kitchen made a mistake.  So the kitchen can‚Äôt even understand orders?  Anyway, is there a minus star?  Google team, we really need some attention here, so many people with bad taste buds or fake reviews are being paid for it?  I am strongly against bad food.  Bad service. For the price doesn‚Äôt even do any justice.

Normal mcdonalds but subsidised prices as it is inside university campus. No dedicated seating as seating is open for mcdonalds, the subway, the long jhon silver's, the starbucks and the food court above

Tried a premium steak set lunch, their chicken skewer, and the grilled squid. Impression for each dish is:
-Premium steak set lunch was a good amount of food for the price but the beef was on the tougher side. I wouldn't recommend this particular set to others.
-Chicken skewer was fantastic. It was juicy and had a ton of flavour. Pretty cheap too.
-Squid was fine. Nothing particularly exceptional either way.

I likely won't be back due to the number of alternative options to try, but if I did go back, I'd just order a bunch of chicken skewers.

I am a fan of the kind of food served at this place. Couldn't find another place in this vacinity with these kinds of cuisines. The sitting area is nice, hygiene is 7 out of 10 for the kind of price they charge but the taste of the food is amazing. This place has noodles as well, but I haven't tasted them. I usually do rice with a few meat options. I usually make my own plate so the price usually fluctuates and the bill always is more than I expected. If you are looking for budget eating instead of making your own plate ask for set with a fix price where you get 1 meat + 2 veg + rice or similar combinations. I will definitely recommend eating at this place.
Chicken cutlet and fish and chips are nice. Old style stall from the 80s but now updated with larger size today. Good stuff.
Love the beers... Loads of options
Must try the white beehoon, super flavourful, it‚Äôs the dry type, one of the best in Singapore
One of the best place for egg and plain prata in Singapore

Amazing ü§©

We ordered the large Hana Bara Chirashi to share (two person) and were surprised by not only the presentation but also the variety of ingredients in it!

Rice were flavourful (not the usual plain white Japanese rice you would expect) and we LOVE the Unagi inside! Didn‚Äôt expect to find it in a Chirashi Don.

Soft Shell Crab were thumbs up to! ü§§

Will be back soon üëçüèª
Really nice staff! Food is prepared when asked, excellent service.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: One of the best Thai Food tailored to Singaporean taste hands down. Portion can be more but still value for money and good good taste üëçüèª will support again üëèüèª
Hw fried tang Hoon NOT oily!!!I don't understand üò≥ü§îüòùü§™
Prata wala says #skipthestraw but they put the curry in a disposable paper container ü§¶
Reasonably priced.  Oyster fried eggs are good.  Pineapple fried rice too wet.

They don‚Äôt accept 5cent coin ü™ô. At first o thought this is invalid to refuse as it is still a money, but after I read the currency act, as long as shop shows the written notice to customers out front, it is legit
Back to their food . Honestly not authentic at all , bean mian was super hard to chew , over stringy??
And char kuetiao is not wok hey .
Only the chendol tasted decent but wish to have more red bean and chendol inside.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Waiters and Waitresses were standing nearby and served promptly whatever necessary and polite. The taste of Crab and fish were from gravy. The fish seemed to be not marinated and the crab seemed to be boiled separately and gravy was poured on top just before serving.
Nice modern bistro with variety of stalls to select and share among friends or family. There are rounds tables suitable for gatherings and chill over wide selection of beers.
very clean environment and good food :)

Lok Lok served here are $1 per stick so if the item has 2 sticks, it's $2.
I would say the food was so-so, not crispy as expected and not really to my liking. All of the Lok Lok are drizzled with a black pepper sauce(?) which wasn't to my liking. Maybe would have like it more without the sauce. They also have sauces which you can grab yourself, satay, chili and sweet chili.
Generally dim sum is ok except for the egg tart.. the egg tart need more improvement.

Rlly love love love the collagen mala soup here! Makes the spice less painful and the soup way more drinkable! They deep fry their potatos and fish to give that crunch and serve eggs in a fluffy soft scramble on top. Super love!

I practically grew up eating this Nasi Lemak. Really glad that makcik is still serving good Nasi Lemak. Definitely love the panda flavoured rice and the chili that goes with it. I will recommend the bagedel from Pak Mandor as well. I thought the chicken wings shrank in size over the years but no complains here =)

Good prata! Very crispy. Even the egg prata was super crispy. The curry was not as good as the prata. I asked for fish curry, but this is not the spicy type. Maybe I prefer those with spicier taste. Since it‚Äôs my first time visiting his branch, I was quite surprise to see people queuing outside the shop before it opens at 8am. A place cyclists will frequent due to the location.

Went for mother day dinner on 7 May 2022 after nearly 2 years of covid restrictions.. enjoyed the food alot üòä

Good zi char place for any occassion. Just finish with early reunion dinner and didnt disappoint üòä

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Good pricing and tasty food...üëçüëç
Yummy Chendol! Thick coconut cream with gula melaka and red beans. Popiah yum also, comes with beancurb and fried egg. Claypot boneless chicken thigh with sambal chilli tasty too

Dim sum experience as close as how its supposed to be. Large seating area with plenty of space. Dim sum quality is great! Love the mini egg tarts especially. Expect to queue especially during weekend mornings where family gather for delicious Dim Sum breakfast.
Super affordable and delicious thick beef patty! So much nicer than another nearby western food. Thumbs up. Returned for their single patty cos dbl is too much for me.
The aglio olio and pork belly are so good taste, price also reasonable, cost me only $11:50
Fresh n generous serving. Delicious  n  value  for money. Way exceeded my expectations.  Nice  experience.

I have my first meal at Papa Jones BBQ and Grill today. The menu is VERY extensive. I choose the Grilled Chicken Chop with black pepper for my first meal here. It's really very delicious. Even my mum, who is with me, can not resist trying the fries. Fabulous cheat food on a day off from my healthy lifestyle.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Food quality is good but dishes come in very long interval.  Have to eat and wait 5, 10mins or longer for next dish.  Rice become cold before we receive last, 3 dish that we ordered.

Service is good, but is good to reserve the seat before heading down for dinner.
Location easy to find and been there for year so mostly people can locate the place
Parking just right behind of the library there is open car park..

Food here is generally good. Portion is generous in most cases. So far I have not tried anything that stands out for me. Service was alright. Not much queueing on a public holiday probably due to COVID. Cost is slightly above average. Ambiance is ok for conversations. Parking is plenty but some distance away.
Standard seems to have dropped during the pandemic. Asked for Medium Rare but Wagyu was cooked to Medium instead. Clam Chowder was shown on menu to be the white, cream based, type but what came was the orange, tomato based, type.

Came here for the Ala cart buffet.  1st round of food served but not all the ordered items arrived.  Waited very long for our food to be served.   Though the waitress and waiters were friendly but the  waiting time was really disappointing.  Will not come again.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Food taste good. good service

Tasty beef rendang.. 2 pax at $13.60. The beef is tough but is very flavourful! The Chili quail egg is not to my liking as it‚Äôs sweet. Other than that the food tasted appetising and won‚Äôt mind go back again..
Had family gathering for dinner. Love their Assam fish head and other dishes. Yummy and delicious. üòãüòã
Great place to chill and have Japanese food üòä
A varieties of halal food available.

My to go loklok place in sg ever since, we can‚Äôt go into Jb. I really like the chilli sauce, not sure why some ppl in the comments will say the chilli sauce is not spicy enough etc etc, personally I love it. If not spicy enough, bring your own chilli.

Do try out the fried mushrooms, it retains the crunch really well, I really like the Enoki wrapped with bacon. And yes, the fried Zai Er. Must wait for it to cool down, and after that the crunch.

The Pork Chop marinate is NICE! Not the usual black pepper or mushroom. The salad was fresh and crunchy, nice sauce with sesame. Plus a generous portion of french fries. They were crispy on the outside and soft on the inside.
Fish & Chips was superb too! The fish fillet was good, it did not have the ugly fishy taste! Haha.
The staff were enthusiastic and smiley. They were extremely happy when we went up to them at the end of our meal to complement the food.
If they serve soup, it would have been PERFECT!
I will definitely come back to try other items, and bring friend when more can dine out.
Do check them out. It is good food at reasonable prices.

Bought the fave deal with the Japanese curry chicken with tonkotsu ramen with just SGD$19.80. Very surprised the food is really nice! The ramen is really Oishi!!! We love this so much. Fully recommend to come and taste.
Good taste
Good food and value for money with entertainer or Burpple 1 for 1. No service charge and GST. Truffle pork chop and ribs were good.

One of the most affordable and delicious Xiao long pao in Singapore.

They used to talk to me only Chinese few years ago.
But this time, all staff are able to speak English.

Had Buta don with onsen egg and Asari Miso Soup. Would be better with more sauce.

I was seated outdoor with live band playing from Tipsy Bunny just beside Aburi-EN. This is a good place to catch up with friends.

Great food, I particularly love the chicken in herbal soup where you can taste the yummy XO taste,  salted egg black pepper crab that's so milky and buttery and the crispy floss egg plant! Super yummy!!! Also, the service staff were quick, attentive and efficient! They even served us complimentary dessert after dinner, such a pleasure to be having my dinner here!

I Ordered Lamb Shank Green Palak gravy with Garlic Naan it was too Good.
The Lamb was very Tender and Juicy.. This was the best Mutton I had in past many years.
The Garlic Naan was also good and went very well with Mutton Palak Green gravy/Soup.

Will visit again soon :)
The food arrives late every blady  time !! I have to wait 15-20 mins for 1 meal & now it's taking longer than 30 mins!!! This is ridiculous!!!
This restaurant keeps improving. The owner provides very good service. It's one of my family's favorite place for prata now.

Terrible place. Order chicken 65, they gave nothing but bone,skin and batter, barely any chicken meat.
Order the mutton claypot rice, come out huge portion of rice but only small chunks of mutton bones and fats, couldnt even taste any mutton meat.

When raise this issue to the staff, this indian lady replied back so rudely saying "you come late, this what we have left"

Wth seriously? If you out of meat, then say dish nt available la! Not give us scraps and leftovers from the kitchen but charge us full price.

FYI, we came to dine in at about 5.30-6ish. I wonder how is that even considered "late" in their minds, when the dinner crowd only started picking up at about 6.30pm after us.

Terribly disappointed with such low quality dish and rude service. My first visit to this restaurant shall be my first and last. Even kopitiam indian shop also serve better quality food. Never coming back to this "Scam-pot" restaurant again.

Service was pretty good. No invasive after ordering and v prompt in topping up tea.
The dim sum was delicious and served quickly over lunch hour. Their liusha bao looks like the baked char siew baos which was surprisingly big and super overflowing with liusha that isnt overly sweet. Good quality of dimsum overall where prices are reasonable. Remember to make your reservations as seats are limited.
Would definitely come back again

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content:
Menu was confusing. It mentioned price per pax serving, but came in big plates.

Fish in the mee goreng was bad, wasn‚Äôt fresh and was mushy. ‚Ä¶

The staff at the restaurant are outstanding. I have known regulars like Ms Leong Tai Yoke for more than 20 years and the service has always been excellent and friendly.
Soup Restaurant serves comfort food at its best. I will be back.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: I have always enjoyed Muslim Delights nasi padang, no doubt about that. Today one of ur servers (tall dark skin moustache guy) gave me attitude when i asked for more gravy as if i owe him a living. As a paying customer, this is not the way to treat your customer, i will appreciate if you can educate this server, thank you.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: The chicken essences really taste good unlike other brands and got me into the pink of health. Customer service was also tip top!
Very lively environment ,nice place to chill and estimating ice cream! Will try another flavour the extra round I am here. Friendly boss too! 5 stars!

Greeted with friendly waiters and waitress, meals are served around 15mins after order.

Ordered bento set and Food were tasty. There were seats during weekday lunch and do not need to wait too long

Ordered from Foodpanda a couple of times. Loving the environmental conscious packaging! and the cute little sincere note with every order, really brings up the positive experience with the brand! Not the most amazing ramen, but it's half the price and the service is awesome so heck yeah I'll support!

Stayed at the Duxton and ate here for dinner one night. Had two different soups (both good but their hot and sour soup was very very good), their signature roast duck (one of the best in town), a tofu dish (forgot the name but goes great with rice) and a simple vegetable (simple but cooked perfectly). We had white rice which came undercooked but we forgave them due to how good everything else was. Noisy and crowded but it was a Friday night so happy we opted for an early dinner. Our only bugbear were the crowds (good for the restaurant but a little worrisome for us in these COVID times). We would have gone back except for that. The duck is probably the best we've had in S'pore.
Good Nasi Lemak at affordable neighbour coffee shop.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Nice Malay food. Pretty pack during lunch time. Go earlier.
Food is good and value for money but service is horrible. Sometimes feel like my mala xiang guo is short changed and ridiculously long waiting time at some times.
The prawn noodle is superb and taste authentic like Penang one. Recommended !

Absolutely huge range of pratas and specialty creations available. I've visited them many times at their Springleaf and Rail Mall outlets, and have found something new to try every time. The Murtaburger is highly recommended!
Love their plain prata and teh tarik. There is indoor aircon seating area and outdoor seating area
Very poor delivery service. Lunch order opening time late. Only at 11.30am.

Nice prata. Specially the plain ones.

Order their Masala chicken. Came later so did not take pic. But it was really good to go with the prata.
Mee Soto and Mee Rebus are always good. Long queue but just be patient and you'll get to order eventually. satay is also very good! Bang for your buck!

Some of the menu rly tasted different from other outlets. They also missed our order and after telling them, they only delivered 2/4 missing orders. Had to let them know again.

Other than that, everything normal.
Not bad nasi Padang, quite affordable as well. Located in a coffeeshop setting not standalone.
My go to place for delicious Chinese food. This place is run by a nice Chinese couple who are always ready to recommend their best dishes.

The best place to get Malaysian food in Singapore. Although it is not super tasty but the taste is there. If you are having homesick and miss Malaysian food, this is the place where temporarily fix your craving. I tried char kuey teow and rojak. Both were not bad. Have to queue for ckt but not long. The other day I had mee siam too ($3.50). Ckt costs at $4.50 for small and Rojak is $3.50 for small. Be prepared to hunt for seats because always crowded as usual and just be patient to look around and wait for the seats. Usually people will leave once they finished their meals.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Good experience at suki-suki Thai serve by Staff Shidah. She's very friendly and attentive. Thank you for the great service.

Good meat, love the karubi, though it‚Äôs a little on the pricey side considering the portion. But meat was well marinated! Four sauces to choose from, seasonings like pepper, and salt.
Long wait though, the queues are usually pretty long!

We arrived at 11am and there was surprisingly no queue. But once we bought our food, a queue formed.

We ordered the small bowl ($4.50) and opted for Ipoh hor fun. Sadly, there was no more fish cake, so we only had the handmade fishball and tau pok.

At first I had commented to my friend that the noodles seemed like a lot. But in the end, I finished them in no time and was scrapping the bottom of my bowl. ü§™

The hor fun was flavourful as it soaked up the sauce. My friend thought it wasn‚Äôt salty enough but it was just nice for my palate. Plus the bits of pork lard gave it an extra kick.

I read a blogger‚Äôs review that the fishball isn‚Äôt as bouncy as others as it is handmade from only yellowtail fish meat and no fillers are added. But I thought it was very bouncy. Not a big fan of the tau pok but I don‚Äôt mind it.

Overall, not bad and will return if I‚Äôm in the vicinity. And I like that the cook and the auntie cashier are friendly. (I dislike hawkers who scold or are rude to their customers and will not patronise them regardless of how nice their food may be.)

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: My fav fish soup in Singapore. Big pieces of fish and the xo soup is delicious. My wife loves the prawn paste chicken. Here we ordered medium fish soup $12 and small prawn paste chicken $12

Been to this place for many meals. Their lunch time promo of 20% discount is so worth it. The Xing Hua Bee Hoon is our favourite for quick lunch. Service is good and prompt too. üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Price wise is standard . Call SHOP TO ORDER AND PICK UP LATER! Shop no. (6816 4463)*ya welcome*
Better then waiting there. Waiting time can be a chore as buzzling with Parton all the time.
I can guarantee this is one of the best parata vendor in Singapore. Parata is crispy and curry is superb.  High standard curry.  Fish curry is properly cooked and thiccc..no comment for mutton coz I can't eat mutton.
There's one more Indian Muslim shop at the other end of junction 9. Terrible parata and curry like add hot water only..very watery. No taste.
This Al fattah eatey is highly recommended.

Spacious with soothing decor, clean and new, comfortable environment. Slightly different concept from their beauty in a pot branches as this gives you individual pots on a burner at your table. I guess it makes it slightly hard to see what‚Äôs in your pot and less options for soup base, but you get exclusivity! Also, they have kindly sorted into sets for the number of pax with all the popular ingredients (yay fried beancurd!) thus you don‚Äôt have to mull over what‚Äôs best to order. You can‚Äôt change any items in the set though.

The sets are really filling and gives you a bit of everything which is really nice. We took a 2 pax set $48.80++ and that excludes sauces ($2.20++ per pax). We added some beef and fried luncheon meats too. Water is not complimentary and chargeable at $0.30++ per glass refillable.

Their soup bases are similar (and more) as paradise beauty in a pot with the exclusion of collagen soup not available for sets. I stuck to my usual tomato (would have loved to have mushroom soup) but would try to be more adventurous next time.

Ingredients provided are fresh and the meatballs are really good and most tasted handmade.

Service is also polite and warm, with service staff constantly refilling your soup or water, and reminding you with little tips.

Do sign up for their membership to get rebates across their entire group of restaurants

Individual set meal of ginger chicken rice portion was small. Individual set of sweet sour pork rice was sufficient, the chrysanthemum drink that came with the set was super diluted like water. Old cucumber soup n cordycep soup were just average. Will not order again.

As mentioned by others a huge problem is a lack of transparency with prices. They just insist on taking your order without being upfront on prices. Same with drinks. Server got the order wrong adding chili to the wrong bowl and rectified it by scooping it out with a spoon and dumping it into another bowl then looking irritated at my surprised expression. Honestly, the noodles are quite decent with a nice texture and the char siew was good with a nice honeyed glaze. Roast pork was too salty. However, this stall will not get anything higher because of the very aggressive staff touting you to eat here and pressurizing you to order without knowing the prices which are fairly exorbitant for what you‚Äôre getting. It‚Äôs a hawker stall but there are still minimum standards of service.
The food are delosh, but the service really slow! Idk maybe they shotage of staff? I ordered 1 plaster took more than 30 min, and people who are come after me get the food 1st!!!
This rojak shop serves the best rojak sauce - sweet, spicy, savoury all at the same time. Very comparable with the big boys at Ayer Rajah Food Centre!

Their staff Christina was excellent. She recommend a new drink Halio O with milk.That was super nice. Her friendliness and good customer service is highly appreciated. You all should come and visid here
Authentic teochew restaurant. Dim sum are served in push cart trolley. We love their Liu Sha Bao, Zhi ma bao, Zhu jiao chu, the rest of the items are also okay. The waitresses are very friendly too.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: One of the better stall in Yishun Park Hawker Centre. Love the fragrance coconut milk rice and fried chicken wing
I like chicken rice set. The mashed potato and cabbage salad is plus to enhence the experience. 5.90 for weekday is reasonable.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Better than Ding Tai Fung ü•≥

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Signature dish - big chunk fried fish meat XO beehoon. Love it to the max. Been frequenting their sister branch at Changi Road for years. Same old great taste. Best with cut chilli padi.
Located at north spine plaza those who visit there don't worry there's alot of food selling there.
Beef burger with 2 sides
Taste and portion size is decent considering the price. Most of the food are cooked on the spot. Stall owner is friendly and will address you as bro or sis regardless of your age.
Pleasant experience and friendly staffs. Food has been consistently good

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: This place is one of those which begs for help during covid but ignore u when business is back to normal. When me and my colleagues went there to eat, we spent about 100 plus with drinks included. While eating at chatting, as long as one person food is finished the waitress immediately clear the plate while others are still eating. It gives the rest of the people pressure to eat faster. Yes granted there was a queue outside but we have been there since covid period to support. But when business oicks up, they keep clearing your plates while others are eating. Hinting to u that u should leave soon. Problem is drinks are refillable for tea at it cost 3dollars per cup. Yet while we are still chatting and drinking they keep the cups too. This for me is too much. Come up to us and tell us that if we are able to go off for them to accommodate people inside to eat. I will not feel so bad. But as a restaurant, you should know people paid for everything including drinks and yet you keep everything to chase us off? Your call if you want to eat there.

Great tasting Teluk Intan food. Have not been there so can't compare but food is value for money at the quality served. Great chillax ambience too, complimented by soothing Chinese MTV. Liked the pan fried chee cheong fan, dry curry noodle, chicken chop nasi lemak, great coffee and the oh so good bean curd.

(Translated by Google) Great fat rice

(Original)
Great nasi lemak

As usual basmati rice briyani but I miss Dum briyani every time I visited..
Nice ambiance and good place to visit with family..

Finally I visited recently and tasted the Authentic Dum Briyanai. Really tastes good and Must try it.
Good service n delicious tze char, signature San lao hor fun lives up to it's name. Minus 1 star because chicken essence frog legs was very tough and rubbery probably because it's frozen
Really the most fragrant rice and chicken wing for Nasi lemak! üëçüèº

The operation/service quality is a disappointment. Brought my family here for dad‚Äôs birthday dinner, ordered some sides & 3 mains within 10mins all the items was served except for 1 main
After asking the staffs to check for us a couple of time the dish finally came! Took a 30mins gap to arrive! The staff (Rachel)black uniform if I see correctly wasn‚Äôt even apologetic when serving it to us üëéüèº
The pork katsu was tougher than my life üôÉ

This is a warning for everyone. For the price that you pay here, you will get non-existent service and food that is worse than what you will get at hawker centre.

From the beginning, their service staff did not care about our needs; half their staff kept glancing at their watch and pretending to be busy. The seating was too close and uncomfortable. The tea was watered down. The sound system broke and was horribly managed.

The food is even worse. The roasted pork was partially uncooked on the inside, with the skin side being extremely tough and tasteless. The appetizers (lotus paste bun and other assortments) looked suspiciously like what I could buy from the FairPrice supermarket cheaply, and were poorly prepared.

The "sashimi" turned out to be cheap raw red grouper that was meant to be cooked in hot soup, which was merely a thin broth with some herbs and too many red dates. The pot's fully metal ladle was left in the boiling soup, scalding our attempts to get it out. In addition, the staff walked around with the burner lit dangerously close to our hair.

The spinach and vegetables set was tough, cooked in a pot of overly salted water using cheap fried anchovies. To add insult to injury, when I brought champagne there, the staff did not care to ensure it was chilled.

The exterior of the restaurant was dirty and wet with what looked like the tossed out leftovers of food. If you are going there, wearing shorts and cheap sandals will be a suitable choice.

All in all, the price you pay at this restaurant ensures you obtain bad service, badly cooked food, and an extremely uncomfortable dining experience. For the same price, you can dine for far better at Imperial Treasures, or a classy Japanese restaurant, or even a well-run restaurant.

You have been warned.

All the dishes are delicious, the best should be the steamed fish..
Price $$
Ingredients are fresh and combinations is great for me!!!

came on 18/3/2022. food took very long to be served. every plate that came, only had 5 pieces. in addition, food was extremely cold and below satisfactory. i am very disappointed. it would be only a 1 time visit for me.
Felt that it was just ok. The green rice is from green coloring and did not have much lemak flavour. Queued for around 20min on a weekday lunch

loved the lobster pasta. lobster cooked well, pasta was flavourful, and exactly how I like it. ordered the set with the mushroom soup which had a hint of truffle scent, as well as the lychee soda which was very refreshing. decent meal with good service!

Rib eye garlic butter medium rare.
The searing wasn't sufficient. It was soggy. The steak itself could do with a little more salting, it was flat.
Still, it wasn't expensive and the curly fries are some of the best I've had.
Where else can you get ribeye for this price?

Yeah the fries are addictive.

Gonna come back for other stuff and order more curly fries.
Good for veg lovers

Terrible service.
First, long waiting time for our group of 6 despite the restaurant being only half full.
Secondly, the PRC waitress had to ask us what we ordered when serving out our food when it eventually came. After that, she even got another table's order for ice water wrong and delivered it to our table!

Only saving grace is its food which is decent.

I will not beat around the bush, the Indian food is really good! This is a little hidden gem in the rough. Not many know about it, but those who do, swear by it. Hands down the best Mee Goreng Mamak and Teh Tarik in the north! I have tried most of their dishes, and none disappoint. Do give it a try if you're around the area!
Their scallion noodles are nice. For Shenjian Bao, skin is too thick. Still prefer the one at Jalan Besar.

Came here for the dimsum buffet. Being a weekday, it was priced at $36.80 (4 diners, 1 diner eats free). The selection was good. However, the eating time is only 2 hours, so it was a bit rushed. The quality of food was normal, reasonable for the price. Good for large groups when u can't decide what to order but not good because of the time limit. Service was good.
Great tasting western food of almost every item listed. I've tried almost all of it. Great curly fries! They serve satisfactory amount of food but not excessive. Affordable neighbourhood prices.

Authentic chinese dumplings that were packed with seafood, meat and vegetables.

Must get dishes are the cheese and rosemary dumplings, as well as the xiao long baos

Malaysia Chiak!
Malaysia boleh....boleh...yeah...

Love the Lontong here.
Even though not the authentic Malaysia version but came quite close.
Remember to ask for the chilly samba, it brings out the full favour of the Lontong soup.
Generous serving of cabbage, Kueh Tupat, boiled egg but the long bean is missing, double check the display photo. Can see the long bean missing from my Lontong?

Comes served in the traditional yellow glass plate. Don't see that kind of plates any more but popular in the 70's in the Malay Kampong.üôÇ

The Chendor beside the Nasi Lamak stall is also my fav stall. Always ask Ice Chendor additional Gula Malacca syrup and NO RED BEAN TOPPING....BUT MUST Have the Green Chendor......mmm...super Manis. This stall Chendor came close to one of the road side mobile mini van Chendor stall in Ipoh in term of taste and texture which I chance upon.

Many choices here, reasonable price. Mee Siam $3.50
Mee Rebus $3.50, Longtong $4, Nasi Leak $3.80. Coffee & Tea weekdays 3-5 pm 80¬¢
Time the management upgrade staff performance too!

Very bad dining experience, the middle age waitress has an unbelievably bad attitude, the set menu omits soup, and no plate was given, there is even a handprint with sauce on the rice bowl, very disgusting!  Some of the meat is cut into very small pieces even leaked out of the grid and burned the grid to black, when we asked to change the grid the waitress was very impatient and directly told us meal time out and we should go, OMG we had just been seated for less than 40 minutes,  Half of the order didn‚Äôt finish and she wanted to kick us out just because we asked her to change the grid! So ridiculous! How did someone with such an attitude become a waiter? Will never go back to this restaurant again!

My husband and I have been hunting for an authentic Yunan crossing bridge noodles in Singapore since we tasted the original ones during our visit to Yunan. Nothing has come close till we visited this place. The noodles and soup are good but the best are still those in Kunming.
The ramen is okay considering the price and location. Broth just lacks alittle extra "umami" flavour.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: Everytime passby this outlet always long queue, happen came early today and buy some of the sushi try try. It was indeed cheaper than other places and salmon fresh too..
Enjoyed the plain dosai. Crispy yet soft. Also bought butter chicken. Quite generous serving.
Many dishes were quite well-executed and prices are ok. The wait is a little long though.
v yummy!! love the fried fish and scrambled eggs üòå

My ramen noodles still have the alkaline taste. Naruto and Iruka would have destroyed this place if they are real. The tonkatsu is decent tho. Overpriced for the quality of food served overall. Didn't get a chance to sit inside and enjoy the ambience as well.

Visited the restaurant during restaurant week. Great ambient and the food was delicious overall. Service was prompt and friendly. Both the Amuse Bouche, Hamachi Carpaccio were full of umami and love it. However, the main couse - wagyu striploin was not the best cut as it is kind of chewy, otherwise, it would be a perfect dinner. The macha panna cotta dessert is a must have and not overly sweet.
The food and variety choices have increased so much. More lively. And good for beer and food.

Came here for dinner.

Food was not bad.
Tom yum soup was good. Spicy, flavourful and slightly sour.
Salted egg chicken was good. Crispy chicken with sweet creamy salted egg sauce.
Thai basil pork was disappointing. It lacked the taste of basil and could be spicier.
Pad Thai was not bad. It was flavourful.
Papaya salad was super disappointing. Lacked the fish sauce to lift up the salad.
Seabass with Thai lime sauce was not bad. The sauce was flavourful and had acidic notes of tamarind which paired well with the seabass.
Red ruby was ok. The ice was too chunky but the red rubies were chewy and tasty.
Thai milk tea was good. Milky and not too sweet.
Lemongrass could use a stronger flavour.

Overall the meal was not bad just need to choose your dish wisely. Prices are also affordable. Would come back again.
The sauce of the noodle is quite different frim Singapore style fishball noodle. With lots of pork lard too. Handmade fishball and fish cake are very Q and chewy.

Food - quality and taste was a 3‚≠ê, as is typical sushi chain restaurants. The variety is quite a letdown. Many of the basic items are not available. The $1 opening promotion for sushi is only on 30 & 31 July.

The wait - ridiculously long waiting time of 1hour for a post-lunch timing and on a Monday. This is partly due to the closure of at least 1/4 to 1/3 of the restaurant and manpower shortage. Any other sushi chain doesn't make customers wait 1h.

Not elderly friendly - from the queueing system to the ordering system, the whole process aren't the friendliest and definitely not elderly friendly. There is no physical menu (except at the entrance) for elderlies to choose the sushi.
Very bad service experience. Why should we eat at a place and feeling annoyed but the unpleasant staffs.

Just returned from the family's first visit to he cafr after we shifted to this area, so we decided to give it a go! Environment was really pleasant, the interior feels like that of a vegetarian dining cafe. The customer's srervice was really commentary- you get alert and friendly staffs. Food is relatively good and we were quite surprised by the portions , certainly sufficient for larger groups. The fried rice on the other hand needs to be improved though ü§™ overall, nice vibes!
Food is nice.
Food was great (sliders were amongst the best we‚Äôve had), ambience was cozy for quiet dinner dates, and the service from Nareenth was top notch! (: will return again to try their brunch menu

Came here for lunch on a weekday. The Captain was super warm and friendly. Tried some new dishes (braised luffa melon with crabmeat and crab roe; claypot snakehead fillet) this round, pretty yummy i might say! Ë∞¢Ë∞¢Èòø‰∫¨Â∏àÂÇÖ„ÄÇ

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
excellent, one of the best Indian food on island.

I 've ordered" family meals"three times already during covid. they deliver to ur House.

Very big, enough for 4 of us, for 2,to3 times meal!
perfect for weekend!

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Good food, for the price extemely worth it.
Service was fantastic... we were kinda late yet the Jov crew maintain professional service level to serve us instead of rushing us.. I really like the different sauces that they made for us.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Newly reopened after a renovation. Not a big hawker centre, but has a few good and popular stalls with a constant line of customers. The food pricing range from cheap to reasonable. The quality is decent, authentic, and sometimes nostalgic. Crowded during lunch hour, and most stalls closes after lunch.

Finally tried the Bacon Carbonara my colleagues always order. Wow... the generous portion of smoky carbon (more like char siew lor... so thick n juicy) stacked on top of creamy pasta is delicious! $9 for such quality! I also love Sausage Mushroom Pomodoro pasta as I‚Äôm more of tomato sauce person. Will keep returning! My dream combo would be this bacon with tomato base!
Nice variety of tasty choices
Japanese fair today Sun 31/1/2012 till CNY 2021 @ Kotobuki Jurong, 3 Yuan Ching Road (Superbowl Jurong).
Nice place to have a family dinner once awhile. Bring your clients to enjoy a local Chinese food. Surrounding environment is good by the big fishing pond at side.

Good variety of food, friendly and efficient staff. The train concept keeps the children engaged and makes dining out fun and different from most other restaurants.

Lost a star as some dishes are on the expensive side - $23 for a beef hor fun dish.

been to numerous ichiban boshi across the island, this one always has the best service. service staff are always warm, friendly, and welcoming. some even check up on you to ask whether the food is alright. imho, if you're at japanese street and don't know what to eat, just go to ichiban boshi. it's the most "worth-it" japanese restaurant to go to at japanese street in jurong point.

All the Dim Sum are really yummy! Alan is a nice and friendly service staff. He recommended me a few special dishes for customer who dine in. I really love the special dishes a lot. Will definitely come back here to eat again in Novena Square TungLok Teahouseüòäüòãüëç

Trying mee goreng at this place.
Food 3/5
Ambiance 3/5
Value for money 3/5

1st time here when the queue was short. Usually queue was very long. So, give it a try. $8 for chicken redang, 1 tempai, curry vegetables and 1 fried egg. Rather expensive. Taste wise ok. Cannot eat frequently due to the high price. But may come again for the taste
Worst. Think twice before you even made purchases with them.

It has been one of my worst experiences here in Singapore for my quest for good Indian food and Biryani. If you get a chance, do yourself a favour and get out. There are better options at B2 food court. Forget about the value for price but the quality of food is not supposed to be served at all. Chicken is very old that it is literally rubber now. Biryani is far below par taste and forget about the overpriced prata and teh!
The Indian rojak is a must try! Eat it with the sauce.

Chanced upon Say Cheese when I was on the way to my grandma's house and decided to try for myself. Was looking for some drinks and the friendly staff recommended me Caramel Milk Tea ($4.50). I topped up $0.50 for cheese foam and the end result was amazing! The caramel wasn't too sweet, which was perfect and the cheese foam complemented the drink really well. Flavour was very balanced and you have the cheese after-taste which was better than I expected it would be :D they have mains on the menu as well, and I will definitely be back again!
Fast and fuss-free experience
Great small eatery with nice food

My parents tried once on their ala carte dishes and it was not too bad. But this second time we ordered the set meal, which was unfortunately not to my liking at all. Have to say the curry fish head is not too bad, normal. But the rest of the dish... is really not my kind of food. Average or slightly below average. Will not return again. I noticed many people are waiting to be seated, probably the taste suits old people more.

Ordered the vegetarian mee goreng found the taste wasn't as I expected from an Indian Muslim stall. The mee is too dry, I prefer slightly oily mee goreng.
The mee goreng found at Yishun hawker centre is much better.
Service bad.
üëç
The service and food is from bad to worse.. 3 simple dishes are served separately with an interval of 10mins in between. Not going back again..

The ambiance is always good even when there are lots of guests. Food has always been delicious. It‚Äôs interesting that the restaurant is bold to revamp its menus every now and then. Thank you for being my family‚Äôs favourite restaurant.

The stall uncle and aunties are all soft spoken with a friendly smile. The mee rebus was tasty and spicy with a tinge of sweetness. They lay on 2 type of sauce on the mee rebus which I think made it very tasty. The pricing was cheap too. My "extra special" plate cost $5plus only. It comes with a chicken thigh meat which taste soft and juicy. Best taste mee rebus in my personal opinion.
In here we get to eat for quite. Amel bros

Decent halal-certified Ichikokudo Ramen with flavourful broth and egg. Broth reminds me of tsukumen. The namban chicken sides was good. Refillable green tea. Not much crowds on weekday lunch.

If u like garlic, the garlic chicken gives the kick along with cloves of cooked garlics.

I'm a long-term vegetarian, and I like to taste the vegetarian restaurant Jiayao in the whole island. This restaurant is one of my favorite visits in the past, but this time I'm very disappointed with their snacks. Among the five snacks I ordered, four of them were filled with the same material, and even the taste and taste were the same! I've never been angry while eating like this time! Because their other dishes are not bad, I am willing to give them two stars! I hope they can see my comments!

Ordered 1 meatball and sliced pork porridge, and 1 pumpkin sliced chicken porridge, have to say both are quite nice and the ingredients are fresh, prices a bit on the high side though. But will eat here again.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content:
Went out to buying dinner and the queue for the sushi üç£store is not very long. My wife took 2 of them and didn't put them in the basket they provided and went to pay.
Back at home, I laid out the sushi on the dining table. Opened up the wasabi and soy sauce.Then it was dinner time.
Each pack cost $4.50 and taste was good enough. Reasonably cheap for sushi. No wonder there is usually, a queue there.

Food was disappointing for the price point. Only giving it 2 stars because it‚Äôs the only fancy place in NTU

Brownie was good
Just plain spicy taste ,not edible, will not visit again. The worst I had tasted in whole of SG
ordered chicken cutlet, thin crispy coated.  coleslaw very fresh and well made, bit stingy on qty..overall food and presentation is good, cutlet well seasoned.
Soup Kambing.... always the best comfort food.  Great taste. All that is missing is the french loaf.
Love it

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Since the closure of Tian Wai Tian at 226 Amk, I tot i could never find another good sweet and sour pork .  I have found my replacement finally here at United Square - Wee Nam Kee! We loved the claypot tofu too.

Had a family dinner here. Food is very good and value for money. Seafood very fresh too. Ordered all these dishes for $235+. Most expensive was the half roasted pig $125. May be a coffee shop but quite windy and not hot. Will definitely be back again.
The place is spacious as they have moved their seating are into one of the ballrooms.

(Translated by Google) Grilled fish, stir-fry, chicken, oyster, delicious, will come again

I took away a set from My Gohan @ Jurong Point Mall today. Only when I arrived home I realized that not all dishes we ordered and paid were given to us. Be careful and check your order if you want to buy food from here.
Recently reopened with a new menu. The $14 set lunch is a good deal. One of the only places in NTU to have food with service other than Cosmo restaurant.
Nice place to eat south and north indian foods in reasonable price and in enjoyable envirement

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
1st time here, on a Sunday evening.
Pretty big place but still got filled up.
They have buffet and ala carte and we went for buffet.

They do missed out an item or 2 of our orders. But not an issue, just reorder it anyway they serve the foods very promptly.

Don't forget the smooth texture ice cream before u leave; must-have items. Hahaha

The butter chicken briyani was fabulous. Love the side dishes too. Not too spicy at all and perfect for someone who is afraid of the spice! Service was a little messy and disorganised with people cutting queues and cashier being too busy with tasks other than taking orders.

Was celebrating my birthday.  Very nice food. At the first was very nice. But small accident with crocoach when the delivery tray send to my desk. But reported to the staff and they had quickly kill and remove the crocoach.  Didn't take the picture as I respect the owner business.
Nice cozy place to have food and drinks. A great place to catch up with friends!
Delicious food at affordable prices! Must try the curry fish head/tail. Nice wok hey for their hor fun. Petai is a must try if you are into it!
it was a fun and interactactive experience.

Just a #simple breakfast at 8am with the Bros... Red bean Jing Jing is damm dope... Well... #drifterdrift have #doneitagain #whoopwhoopwhoop

For @drifterdrift and @igymtoeatmore for more information
Not so good!Find seat to eat also problem.Crowded and cramp place to enjoy ur food.

Got the lunchtime menu items of bangers and mash (sausage slices and mashed potatoes, which was not what the picture showed), sirloin steak and chicken and pork adobo. All 3 items were mediocre at best. Everything was covered in brown sauce. Couldn‚Äôt taste anything of the meats at all. The sirloin steak was too tough and a tad dry. Same with the braised chicken and pork adobo. Braised meats should not be tough. The sausage slices just tasted like rubber. I would never be back for the food.

The menu was old and dirty. Pictures were terribly grainy and not representative of the items. The wooden bottom upon which the hot plate for the steak, was broken.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Prices are cheap. Food quality is mediocre. The amount of ice in the drink tower is amazing, basically you are drinking very diluted stuff. Go if only you are looking at cheap Mookata.
Prices is reasonable, owner friendly
The portion is quite small and it was about 10 dollars for a curry don which is overpriced and the food was not that impressive.It is halal.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: One of the best indian restaurant in Singapore... Where you can have wide varieties of delicious food with affordable prize..
Difficult to find a local restaurant. They have some awards for the chicken that was super tender, but we loved the dim sum (shitake&truffle was amazing) there.

Quality of the food: 4/5
Service: 5/5
Environment: 5/5
Value for money: 4/5
Overall: 4.5/5

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Good food. But located in a corner that is not easy to find.

Went there for lunch and ordered that Hana Bara Don S$28.50+ but was not expecting to wait 45mins for the food. Suprisingly the presentation of the don is pretty appealing, with generous portion of assorted raw fish cubes, foie gras, sakura ebis, tamago, cucumber & edamame, etc.  with the wasabi and ginger and they taste fresh. The little negative is too much of foie gras which make the whole bowl very greasy.
Good food. Very reasonably priced. Definitely will return for more.
Freshly cooked
Loved the nasi lemak taste and especially the chicken wing. Sedap!

Has a wider menu selection than your regular Soup Spoon outlet, so you can also have other western food options beyond just soup! Food was good, but you need to order using a kiosk, which was a bit fiddly as one of the menu items on the main signboard we wanted wasn't available on the kiosk and we spent a bit of time tapping around looking for it, so knocking off 1 star for that
Very affordable and also healthy

1. most of the staff were good, but one of them, Yi Qiu was mean and ignorant. we tried so hard to order the food and had requests like taking photo, but she ignored us when we asked 3 times.
2. one of the dish, the roast duck, was not roasted well enough. it was frozen meat and the texture was too hard. i wouldnt order it if i were you.
3. what kind of establishment is this? no tablecloth and the table is dirty. i pay for expensive service charge and the food is expensive, but i do not receive equal amount of service that i paid for. i mean seriously? if i walk into a high paying restaurant, paying 8 dollars for service, at least set up a new tablecloth to give me good hygiene!!

Very basic eating joint. Nothing special not seem to be hygienic.
North indians might not like.
Dosa for 3$ , only Sambar no chutney

Nestled away at the foot of a HDB block, with ample parking. Food was good, fried egg was done really well but a little too oily. Tom yum soup (clear) was good.

Service from the staff was mixed - the lady taking orders was incredibly curt, but the servers were friendly and helpful. It is a good place for simple, fuss free Thai fix.

Ordered Prata and iced teh tarik.
Affordable price, waiting time reasonable as prata is cooked fresh. Love the fish curry.

Ordered masala thosai and iced teh tarik yesterday, costs me 4.50. coconut chutney was really good.

No photos coz I forgot. Hehe
Great dumpling house and Chinese food. Must rry the soup dumplings as they were amazing.

I placed a pre-order at 9:30am to be delivered at 6pm, and my order was cancelled at 5:43pm without any form of communication. When I tried to place an order again, they cannot be found on Foodpanda anymore.

The service at the restaurant is Terribly bad and slow. My takeaway order of ONE dish took almost an hour. Needless to say, I saw many helpless diners waiting in vain for their food today in the restaurant. In particular, the cashier's service is very bad and rude. I recall that she used to be a staff at the previous Chicken-Up restaurant. I used the CDC voucher as I saw that they accept it. However, the cashier insisted that I had to 'round up' the charges rather than be able to use a combination of CDC/cash to make the exact change. A case of cheating the customer   a case not respect government CDC voucher

Was quite authentic on its opening. Over the years felt like the taste has been altered to suit local palate. The must eat would be the standalone chendol stall near the middle island (with fake trees), best chendol in Singapore.
Good and affordable Japanese Bento, Ramen,Soba and Don.
Sirloin Steak and Chicken cutlet are good and highly recommended. Chicken Chop is average but lamb chop too dry. Overall is good but repare to wait if reach after 6pm in weekend.

Love that it's open round the clock! Soup is good and really affordable, fish slices are fresh too. Ordered fish head steamboat, one sweet sour pork (in ice), a couple dim sum and red bean pancake for 6, less than 15 per pax

1 Star - Lots of Friesü§î
Very disappointing when being given 2 halves of 2 different proportion sizes half spring chicken when I ordered 1 whole spring chickenüòî
Gave me a dry out half spring chickenüôÑ
If there's no whole spring chicken, then remove from your menu. Offer buy 2 halves with $3 offü§î
Still have to pay extra 30¬¢ for your advertisement boxüßê

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Liu sha bao ($4.50) that doesn't liu. Imagine my disappointment when i bit into the bao to see solid bits... but the liu sha does taste great! Only pity is that it's too small.

Menu doesn't indicate price so it is inconvenient to make payment. The staff took my order while standing far inside the stall. She shouted the price $4.5 but somehow i interpreted as $3.8 and made the payment on Grabpay. It was only few minutes after my payment that she walked over to where I was sitting to tell me that i underpaid. She also didn't validate at my point of payment. Stall owner should consider indicating the price on menu.

Simple setting Japanese‚Äôs restaurant at affordable price. Came here for bento lunch set at $19 with sashimi , fried chicken , rice, soup and vegetable. Fresh sashimi and tasty chicken. They served many other Japanese style food and worth a try. Simple and tasty.. will come for dinner too!

Updated with latest visit after 1 year.. jan 2021. Came here for lunch with my loved ones, enjoyable lunch with great deal 1 for 1 using some apps. The tempura curry udon was tasty and no overpowering. Perfect Grilled of hamachi cheek, spider maki were great but the katsudon kind of average as the chicken meat is too dry ! Loved the gyoza with perfect crisp outside and moist inside made perfect !

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Very nice food,will definitely come again!

This is my first visit to Xing Hua. The first thing that attracts me is the simple but clean and bright interior. Also their variety of dishes esp the Heng Hwa bee hoon & Putian dishes are mouth watering. I was there at 4.00pm and their staff services were very friendly and professional. I will bring my family next week for lunch.

I'm surprised that both the pork noodles n kampung chicken are quite good, especially the pork noodles which is full of ingredients. Not bad for a $5 bowl of noodles and $4 for the plate of chicken.

Will come back next time for the fried kuayteow, claypot rice, hokkien prawn noodle soup which all have a long queue.

A pity that this is located at B1 and all the way at the far end of Northpoint City. Hopefully more ppl will patronise and support the biz.

This stall sells street-style western food and their chicken chop is one of the favorites here. The chicken chop, was lean yet tender enough, retaining its tasty juices. It was topped with their custom made mushroom sauce, which is addictive, super delicious and fragrant.

Fish and Chips at $5.50, you will get 2 crispy fish fillets, coleslaw, baked beans and a fried bun. The fillets were crispy on the outside and succulent on the inside, I was pleasantly surprised that it tasted great and old school.

Fried Chicken Cutlet at $5.50 too, was a no frill, old school type of western food.  Freshly deep fried in a wok of hot oil upon order and served immediately with the sides. The cutlet has a thin, golden exterior crust which was exceptionally crispy, and the meat was tenderly and juicy.

It brings back wonderful childhood memories. Kudos to the stall owners and hope they keep this old-school western food tradition going on.
Nice various types of yummy malay halal food. Fast service.

I have seen this around for many years and I regret not trying this earlier! We had one Hae Bee 5 Treasures which is huge in portion. Loves the Hae Bee rice balls and the soya chicken. Ordered one curry rice bento which came with lots of chicken (thigh) and curry. Even the potatoes are perfectly cooked and soft! We were so full we can‚Äôt finish everything. Will be back!

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
I've only eaten at this joint and my review is for this outlet only.
I had their set K. They really nail it for their chicken. Grilled chicken that's moist and juicy,  but beware of the chili on it. The spiciness kicks in later... But it's so good you can't help but surrender yourself to it even when knowing it'll bite u later!

And the staff, they are just.... HAPPY. The positive vibe from the crew just makes eating there a joy!

A pleasant find in Ang Mo Kio area, which had a quiet environment for group meals. Service is good and fairly fast. Chinese dishes are generally tasty. Their signature duck is good, especially the Peking duck. Enjoyed the vegetable dishes, which weren't oily nor laden with monosodium glutamate. Doesn't leave you feeling thirsty after the meal.
It was a bit hard to navigate around when inside the ITE but other than that it was quite a pleasant experience! Love the char siew and sio bar. Very cosy restaurant, suitable for family dinner!

I ordered a plate of chicken chop, my daughter a plate of pork chop.
Portions are big and generous.
Sauce is dilute and I have tasted some better ones
Meat is good.
Overall good.  Not exceptional though, my fussy taste buds tell me :-)
Nice Thai food. But I feel maybe can adjust prices for HDB based Thai resto.
Very classic restaurant inside an old building maxwell chamber. Restaurant are well decorated n food are fusion type.

Not sure why the rating is so low. The claypot chicken rice is really decent, with the rice just nice (not too burnt, but crispy), adequate amount of salted fish, and the chicken was well marinated, albeit a lot of bones.

Quantity is also generous, like typical claypot rice places. The medium can feed 3 girls.

Chilli was not bad too.

Service is abit slow after ordering, approximately wait for 15mins.
The fried dim sum, example fried seafood bean curd, alot of grease drip when bite. Overall, food tasting not worth the price. Too expensive.

Chanced upon this on Google maps which is near my place. This ramen is restaurant standard, but just located in a coffeeshop. Even bowls and plates used are those you usually use in a restaurant.
Price point is for sure lower than those in restaurant, but the type of ramen variety seems to be only those few. They sell fried rice menu as well.

Broth is thick and good, I like it a lot. Chashu is slightly tasteless, but it's to my liking. Feels fatty and seems like will melt inside your mouth. Eggs are the runny kind as usual, and the seaweed or nori is super huge. They have black fungus as well. If they could add bamboo shoots I think that complements the taste.
Special mention goes to the gyoza. Steamed but fried on one side. It's juicy as well, so once you bite it, the juice oozes out.
Recommend if you are nearby üëçüèæ
Tabao their Fried rice with pork chop @ $6.80. Good and not expensive.
Love the embience in Bishan park. Enjoy the big cooling air even in outdoor sitting. Service is good. Food is tasty. Nice place for beer, sake, in the late afternoon.

Feels like being transported back to an old izakaya in Japan (now that we can‚Äôt travel). Set lunch was good with free coffee, nice ambience, service is good. At night it turns into an izakaya. A rare find in that vicinity.
My family loves it! But the seller is very stingy with the soup, doesn‚Äôt not give us soup when we order DRY noodle takeaway.

Is this some slow western food stall?? waited over half an hour to beyond fifty minutes just to take away a packet of fish & chips. Slow service indeed, gave up and went home empty-handed without paying them.
Food tastes good. A different kind of butter taste for prawn and different kind of sweet and sour pork taste for the rib pork.

Convenient place to walk from the MRT. Ordered the signature rice noodle. I like the lightness of the broth. You can tweak the spicy level by adding their in-house chili sauce. Overall unique Chinese food, which you don‚Äôt find in other places in Singapore.
not bad but Mutton Curry too salty. Portion is small, price abit in higher side. Suitable for people who are not so hungry as a supper.
Chaos in the ordering sequence. Dine-in expect to wait 40mins when all orders went to Grab and FoodPanda
Very nice üëç. Is a must try. Very reasonable pricing. Very friendly staffs. 10 of us eat whole hearted under 76 dollars!

Good selection of vegetables, unlike some Indian restaurants. I liked the tofu sambal and the mutton. The mutton especially was flavourful and cooked just nice. Kedongdong juice had an interesting taste and was refreshing. Service was polite and prompt, though they did struggle when there was a crowd. Overall, we had a good, affordable meal. Definitely worth a try.

2nd visit there. Surprising find. Very nice Thai food. 1st visit we had their abacus seed, roast pork kway chap and lala bee hoon. All very good. Way above average and the abacus seed had an interesting twist to the non Thai ones.

This visit  as the sambal fried kway teow came out first it overpowered everything else. Highly recommended!! But if you are eating other dishes, taste the others first!
It's ok

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Great Hunan cuisine. Service a bit slow, and communication in English not always easy. A wonderful and tasty experience. Will come again.
Love the experience here. Free salad bar, amazing food and good service. Love this place...

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content:
(Translated by Google) highly recommended! Good location, good food, good chilli, serviceüëçüèªüëçüèª
Fair price üòäü•∞!
