restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
With so many Indian restaurants around the place, Anjana‚Äôs stands out with their service and taste. They take order from each one of us and treat us like family which is a rare quality now. And, both south Indian and North Indian dishes taste delicious thanks to the authentic chefs. One Mr.Ranjan does amazing North Indian food. Just ask him what he wants and he whips his magic around and creates world class food.

P.S. Their complete vegetarian meal is packed with so many items and is priced at only $6.5

Chance upon this Xiao Chi shop as the intended jap restaurant was fully booked. I must say I dislike thick noodle but the minced meat noodle is so ‚ÄúQ‚Äù and delicious. The dumplings ü•ü are juicy and the filling tasted great dipped with vinega ‚Ä¶

Creamy trio egg porridge
Thai style fried tofu
Same good quality food and service as their other locations. Extensive menu, reasonable price, good quality ingredients, prompt service.

Bought 1 piece of Kueh Kaswi and One piece of ondeh ondeh..both the size of a 50 cent coin...was charged 0.80 each.  This was my first time buying the kueh from there and will for sure be my last time.  Way tooo Expensive. I can get a better deal elsewhere.

Had dinner at the new compass one stall. The chicken is good. You must try the chicken when you are there. Ordered other dishes and found them too be good as well. I will surely return for more of the chicken rice.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: My fav teochew restaurant at all times! Still good quality and service top notch! High price though but worth it!
The staffs working there were so rude lol. Didn't even acknowledge our presence , just continue to do their own chores. Nani, customer service just atrocious.

The ckt was not too bad, but could have used a bit more wok hei.  Waiting time was about 10 minutes, and you can get a ice lemon drink or a lime juice for $1 with every order.

Some reviews commented on the claypot rice.  We did not try it, but there was a table that ordered 11 portions.

Price 3/5
Food 3/5
Ambience 3/5
Overall 3/5

Price is pretty much reflective of the food. The prata taste like an average prata, but I love the big bag of papadom they have. The papadom sells at $1.20.

Curry is the watery type, mildly spicy.

Had the teh halia. Ginger taste is mild, tea isn't very sweet unlike usual Muslim restaurant where the tea is diabetic.

Will return here if I'm craving for some prata while around this area. Otherwise wouldn't make a special trip down to this place.
Quiet place to have a meal during weekdays. Food quality is good and price is reasonable.
Nice food if u are in the area, toilet is abit old school.
Quite an experience to grill with a variety of meatüòô premium selection for amateur grillers are tough as we don't know how to cook it the "proper" way üòÇ P.S. my mom burnt her wagyus.
Above average. Fishballs were super q. Other than that, nothing special for me.

Plenty of parking lots outside. Service staffs are polite. Don't like that they ask you to get appetisers even before we started looking at the menu. The appetisers were $6 char siew (abt 10-12 pieces) and $2 steamed peanuts. Wet tissues at 30cents. I ordered $10 steamed chicken which seems not enough for 2 pax. Oil rice is nice but quantity is small. Their chilli is quite hot. Might not return. 925 yishun chicken rice has better steamed chicken.
breakfast is good :') but cld have more options

Service and ambience is good but I feel that the price is on the high side since the Trio Sauce Chicken had many pieces of bony chicken for $14. Taste is OK.
Best dish for us was three egg vegetable.
Hokkien mee was OK too but not much ingredients.
Overall, I think you are paying for the setting and service.
We were impressed by how delicious the plant-based option was, ramen was also good.
The penang Laksa is delicious and generous serving of ingredients.
Had a lovely dinner and thank you Ms Berlin koh for the awesome service.

Japanese restaurant serving yummy simple food, located in scenic Ang mo kio- bishan park.  Lovely alfresco area & great for a stop before or after a walk in the park.

We had light bites which was the skewers & they were great
Chicken tsukune with onsen egg gives a refreshing take on the item as well.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
The Damage: S$10-15 for two

Medium sized hawker area on the second floor of a market complex. Popular with residents around the area with hits including the Bib Gourmand Carrot Cake and Hokkien Mee stall

~~TRYüòç:
// Come Daily #02-27 ~ Hokkien Mee

Follow us at IG: eatsmorefun

Had a very bad experience last week. I wish I could give 0 stars.
Went to buy takeaway for 3 portions of fried rice but was treated with absolute disrespect by the female Chinese cashier. Rude and disrespectful, slammed the receipt on the table and rudely shouted at me to take it while I was preparing to pay.
Will not patronise this shop ever.
Nice & reasonably priced. It's a small restaurant selling 'xing hua' dishes.

Wow.. very nice pau..i bought red bean and big chicken pau.. both very tasty... Stuffingüòãüòãüòãüòã..
Recomme ‚Ä¶
The cheapest and best place to have Indian food in Singapore if you are close to Pioneer or NTU.

Was in the area at abt 2.30pm and read the good google reviews. Hence decided to try out as the place was empty too.

Ordered the $5.50 egg fried rice and pandan leaf chicken. Cashier mistakenly keyed as pork chop fried rice. Nvm I just go along to see if the higher price of $8.50 is worth it.

Verdict: Overrated & overpriced food for total damage of $10

Pork chop was really tough, not crispy at all and taste bland.

Fried rice got nice 'wok hei' yet was bland as well. Normal coffeeshop tze char's fried rice taste better at lower price.

Saving grace was the pandan leaf chicken which was not bad. But it was a extremely tiny piece which didn't justify the $1.50 price.

Furthermore, even if u dine-in, the food is served in paper boxes and disposable cutleries are used. Might as well do take-away only.

We always enjoy the steak and pasta here. The steak is accurately done to our liking and in our opinion value for money. Last night we had the different meat combi which allowed us to taste beef from different origins w/o breaking the bank. Service was friendly and good.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: chicken rice overalls ok. but roast pork belly totally disappointed. taste dry, no crunchy, cold like bring out from freezer. is overnight left over. will no more next visit.
The best affordable Japanese cuisine ever! Tempura here is pure perfection.

Ambience is alright, has a tacky industrial look. Menu is really quite extensive and includes a whole range of ice cream flavors but I only tried the coffee.

Got a long black and a flat white and when the drinks came, I could not tell them apart because there was that little foam in the flat white. Their coffees do not come with latte art, just milk dumped into the espresso shot. Taste is not too bad but the there is a lot of room for improvement wrt the texturing of milk.

Cannot comment on the service as we ordered through the phone app instead of at the cashier.
Very bad, not open, lazy staff don‚Äôt want cook prata for me
Very kind uncle serving us ‚úåüèøthe plain Prata alone, with special fluffy texture  is worth our trip to here.
Good food! At the middle of the night it is one of the most perfect supper place!
This is the worse Japanese food stall ever ..lots of msg .. total failure . Pls don‚Äôt TRY.

Ate the tomyam w chicken, mango salad, olive  fried rice and Thai milk tea. Food not bad taste very authentic the chicken from tomyam taste like my mum's cooking and it has both sourness and spiciness but a bit too spicy for me and mango salad has many small shrimps inside taste very flavourful not like other places where they just dump mango inside but is also a bit too spicy for me.  Next time I will ask for less spicy. The olive fried rice taste alright nothing special just taste like fried rice from a tze char stall
Best steamed fish ever. Been patroning this joint at least once every two weeks. üëçüèª

Went at 2pm weekday Wednesday and ordered Set C. It consists of 1x Jjampong(spicy noodle), 1x Zhajiang noodle(minced pork dry noodle), 1x large plate of fry Sweet sour pork with refillable simple banchan of kimchi, onion and pickles. Jjampong was spicy taste good but only onions and 3 small pieces of squid. The dry noodle was atad too oily but the crunch frehs kimchi and pickles neutralise it. Sweet sour pork was medicroe nothing to shout about. Overall costed $50 but would not go back to have as tried others w similar Priceline in sg with much better taste and more ingredients(eg. Hwang sil).
Quite standard DTF. Great, friendly service. Long queues during peak hours.
Good food and fast service. Yam and bee hoon were amazing, definitely should order this two dishes when visiting.
My favourite ikan bilis satti soru. Slightly expensive but big portion. Reccomended to share by 2 pax. Love the ice cream too.

Good place to eat a substantial meal. They have set meals as well as individual items. Vegetarians can also find some dishes / meals for themselves. Prices are quite reasonable and portions are large. They can improve upon their cleanliness. Single wash basin in a narrow enclosure needed scrubbing.

A 10-15mins walk from AMK Station, located in Ditjsun Mall.  First time there and I love the food there! The staffs are also friendly and quick to serve. Got the Double up black pepper grilled chicken and the fried one. The portion was pretty big compare to Astons! It was very filling for both me and my bf. We also got the tom yum crab pasta which is very creamy and has the subtle tom yum taste and it is not overwhelming compared to other Tom Yum pasta. We both added $6 for the set meal (mushroom/minestrone soup , garlic bread and root beer float). Overall the dining in was a pretty good experience. There's GST and service charges but compare to other Western restaurants it is still affordable. Can get the double up chicken and share with your other half too! Would definitely go back!

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: A decent place to have prata. Have to work on cleanliness. Price is reasonable. Food is decent. Limited seats.

The freshness you can taste (and have to wait for). Everything is simply cooked but because it‚Äôs fresh, the taste is different from (and better than) other famous Nasi Lemak places, the chili from Changi Village and Adam food center are still better though.
Try come early before lunch, the first time we came here to try at late lunch hours the stall was closed, and I can only imagine the queue is even longer at noon.
Amber and ËÉ°Ááï are very pleasant and attentive. Both will look into what we need and provide and serve well. Frequently top up our drinks. üëç

Nostalgic old school feel to the place adds to the good traditional flavours. Pay after eating. So far only tried and like in order of preference byriani with butter chicken ($6), curry chicken ($6), lamb shank ($12.9). Byriani rice is light and separated well, not clumped together. IMO the prata is also good - my goto place now for prata for taste, portion and price ($1/pc for plain).  IMO sufficient portion for the price across the menu. Place appears to struggle with volume though... did I say old school. Hope they keep the taste, qty and ingredients if/when they do modernise the sales system.

Good sushi in the heartlands! Went here with my wife as we were craving for sushi. Have to say, we were pleasantly surprised at the high quality food and service.

As soon as we were seated, it felt as if we were transported away from the heartlands with the high class decor and atmosphere. The service was top notch with each staff being very welcoming and prompt. The sushi and sashimi were delectable and tasted fresh. My wife went with their Udon which had a very delicious broth and springy noodles. I went with the Yakiniku Don and it had strong beefy flavours and savoury sauce.

Don't sleep on their dessert offerings too, this is one you won't want to miss! The Matcha ice cream was great but I can't stop raving about their Chocolate Wafer! Vanilla Ice cream with great quality thin chocolate bar in the centre sandwiched between wafers - every bite kept me wanting more and luckily for us, the portion was very generous.

Overall, I highly recommend a visit here if you're ever craving for great Japanese food.

Below average food at expensive prices. The only good thing is shorter queue and higher chance of getting a seat. Male cashier is rude and customer service can be greatly improved. We pay to enjoy our food and not to be treated badly and be stared at.

Came on a weekday night. Not much queue and food came quite fast. Big portions for each order. One portion definitely enough for two small eaters. Pad Thai was flavourful and pineapple rice come with lots of pineapple. üëç
Quality of food has declined. What is that Michelin guide about? Plus - the cockroaches outside their establishment? Avoid this place. Mediocre tzechar fare at restaurant prices
Such a fun place to go eat at. The food simply tastes so delicious. It is the perfect place to stop at to get a quick bite to eat. I recommend to get the chicken balls, they are by far the best.
Prices increase main course costs at least $20 now. Fish is hard and chewy??!! Best is their whole calamari very soft with smoky taste, won‚Äôt come back again

normal indian muslim food...prices used to be ok ...but it has gone up.
ice water is now 50 cents a cup up from 30 cents before.

no more smoking area too.
so smokers take note.

Let me just quickly state that parking is going to be a pain. We had to park at the nearby HDB estate and walk over.

We had the prawn claypot with glass noodles which was slightly disappointing as there was no burnt taste that you would normally associate with a claypot dish. The prawns and noodles were cooked fine.

The grilled pork cheeks were quite nice although it was 99% fats.

The prawn cakes were perfectly done, light and fluffy on the inside and crispy on the outside. Easily the best dish.

Personally I prefer the outlet at sim lim but this place was quite decent.
I had mee rebus with begedil, it was tasty. However I noticed it came with half a hard-boiled egg, also for mee siam. IMO for the pricing, I think it should be a full hard-boiled egg.
Nice food with reason price

Portion very small.
Love the spring roll, noodle and crispy pork.
Need to call and reserve

Just bought the Umi birthday Don set from this outlet today at 7.25pm, it was so disappointing because my Onsen egg was broken, there was insufficient sauce for both rice and the chicken and worse of all, the 'fresh greens' were definitely not fresh! The broccoli in particular tasted sour, and it wasn't the vinegar kind of sour, but the sourness that comes from food gone bad. As I stayed nearby, I returned to the outlet at around 9pm with my bento, to feedback to the staff at the outlet about the sour broccoli. The staff replied me that the sourness was probably came from the wafuku sauce added. I explained to the staff that it was only the broccoli that tasted sour and no other part of the bento, which would not be the case if the sauce was added to the bento. The staff took my bento over and looked at it for a good 2 seconds and then asked if I wanted him to throw it away, with no other follow up action like checking if the existing stock of vegetables did go bad. This is my first time trying the bento and it was definitely not worth my time, or any others for the matter!
Ramen is quite nice and the price is reasonable
Individual hotpot, selection not as much as "beauty in the pot ÁæéÊªãÈîÖ", price about the same.

While the seating area is air-conditioned, the queues are usually very long during lunch and dinner. Service is often slow thanks to low number of staffs and a lack of self-ordering machines (Sometimes there is only 1 staff at the counter, who has to collect money and pick up the food/drink items all by himself/herself.) Items in this branch are often out of stock, and there is no indication of items running out. Hence it is annoying when I realise my desired item is out of stock after queuing for more than 15 minutes. (In McDonald's, out of stock items are indicated on the menu screen and blocked on the self-ordering machines.)

Update (07 Sep 2018): There are 2 self-ordering machines at the entrance now, but they only accept card payment. When I was there, nobody was using the self-ordering machines and there were more than 10 people queuing at the counter. I ordered through the self-ordering machine and surprisingly I received my food within 5 minutes, while the queue at the counter didn't seem to move at all. (There were only 2 poor staffs manning the counter and preparing the orders.)

On my first visit here, tried the lamb üêë shoulder with sweet potatoes. You can smell and taste the charcoal üôÇ so pretty satisfied. Been back regularly. Great stuff. For sides I'd recommend the pasta or sweet potatoes.
üíØ best delicious food. Must try thier seabase 3 rasa fish dish and Nasi Goreng Kampung. I will consider the best in Singapore .

The staff here keeps getting the orders wrong.
Not sure if they are under staffed or slow.
Some of the staff here are rude too.

The food is okay...it's McDonalds üòÇ

Menu offer is simple, neat and clear. Sushi rice is done just nice and taste moist. Although it‚Äôs at slightly pricier side, but the ingredients offer on sushi is fresh. But some types are quite saucy but probably it‚Äôs cater for general crowd. Can come back and try their noodle, rice and appetizers. This train concept is good as increase in efficiency in delivering the ready dish on table. So that customer can finish save time.

Hi today i went here with my family to have lunch. The WORST!!!!!!! FOOD i ever ate super duper LOUSY BRIYANI fake dum briyani and fake butter chicken. The chicken is very dry tasteless  sound like almost rotten food they serving . BUTEER CHICKEN IS FULLY OF FOOD COLOURING AND  BONE VERY LOUSY FOOD. LUCKY I NEVER TRY ANY OTHER DISH. Not worthy for money and please AVOID to go there . Super lousy food and service so disappointed

Ordered the half jampong n half jajangmyeon.
The portion is huge and almost x2 of normal size. The jampong is spicy and jajangmyeon has strong taste of onions as the sauce has lots of onions.

While the taste is authentic but the cooking taste is not my preference.

However I like to say the customer service is very good. And a lot others seem to like as its full house even on wkday lunch.

Ordered the premium steam don, beef was super dry and rare, making it tough to chew. Miso soup tasted like those instant packet soup, and the grilled vegetable was probably the most decent thing there. First and last time, not recommended.

Hidden at a popular heartland area, this gem definitely serve up a good bowl of ramen. Broth are fantastic but the noodles are a little lacking. The convenient location pretty much makes up for it though!

Would have given it 5 star if their self ordering kiosk accepts credit card as a payment method.
Have been coming here regularly for my claypot rice cravings. Although portion seems to have become smaller, but the quality is still good and the medium sized is good for two
Rare gems, surprise taste and fairly priced. Will come again!

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Tried their 4 pax set meal around $350++ plus their famous duck and fried oyster. Overall I like their garlic lobster and spinach with abalone. Their CNY Yusheng also quite special, unlike the conventional one.

Really like the batang fish porridge as the soup is thick and tasty, alot of fish. $12 for 2 person and should be enough for 3 person. Tim sum is handmade, 20% discount after 10pm. No gst or service charge and is open 24hrs.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Management was bad we waited for 2hrs plus and they told us there were no seats but we saw them giving the seats to other people üò°Also before we when there we called and asked if we could book in advance they say it wasn‚Äôt allow rly bad managementüò°

Food is hawker price but portion is half. $4 for tiny bowl of prawn mee and assam laksa. Assam laksa never put prawn paste and not nice. Prawn mee is ok. Kl hokkien mee is good and $6. Wantan mee not good, and their wantan was not ready. Crowded only because of the novelty and good location

LOUSY  is an understatement.  Steak made super well done despite ordering medium rare. Ask for a change, told by the stall guy, there is no difference between medium well & medium rare. What??? Do you even qualify to do steak when all wellness means the same???

There was lesser queue on a Wednesday 2pm. However, the varieties are seriously lacking. Many popular items were not available. Sushi was not even cold. That said it‚Äôs edible but the portioning alone didn‚Äôt even feel satisfying. Not just any rice & seaweed makes sushi.

Mentai Aburi salmon was barely torched and looked pathetic with the salmon wrapped around the rice. It was also overwhelmed by the amount of mentai sauce on top.

Kani salad gunkan looked fresh with the crispy looking seaweed but all the goodness ended there. Salad was warm and not even delicious. Just meh.

Sushi express had better standards. Feels like $1 promotion has caused them to cut corners leading to unsavoury  and warm sushi. Save your money for something better.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
With so many good reviews, i can only guess we may have ordered the wrong dishes.

Btw the even the chicken rice is lack of fragrance.
Great Malaysian hawker food options. Duck is yummy with kuay teow soup, ramen, char kuay teow, chendol, popiah

Totally immerse with the Tom yam soup! Especially when days that you are feeling down, hotpot at paradise will never go wrong!

The best time to pop by are during lunch and tea time, to make your money worth while! since they are having promotions! But not to fear, always call to make reservation for weekend dinners (Friday, Saturday, Sunday)

Did a company event here years back and the service is really üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª. As a fan of hotpot, I will recommend here as compare to those Buffet style. Good food, good service, worth coming!

I tried the $18 set meal which was promoted as for one person (set comes with 1 rice). Expensive considering this is just a stall in coffeeshop and that one of the three dishes was just deep fried omelette. The other 2 were tom yam soup and stirred fried mixed vegetables. Dishes were rather salty as they were not light on using fish sauce.  Perhaps it is just my preference. Fish (1 pc) and prawns (2 pcs) tasted not fresh. 3 stars given because of low score in value for money, seafood in tom yam soup lacking freshness, ok taste only and long wait.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Always bring friends to this mookata stall cos we can both order mookata and the mala then we can share (:
Not much prata place left. Quite good too

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: 1st time try this wanton noodle and I was very happy about it.  The char siew is well roasted and costed with a layer of honey.  Noodle is al dente.  Saurce is just right too.
Best food in town good service recommended buta donüòã
Love this restaurant.  Went 3 times in Dec with different group of friends.  Tried a few different dishes and all taste good.

(Translated by Google) It's full of bugsüêõ, the sanitation is extremely poor, and the service attitude is the lowest on the island! ! ! !

(Original)

Nice soft dory, potato wedges piping hot! Yishun outlet

Nice Chinese restaurant, walking distance from tanjung pagar MRT, Exit A.

We had our lunch here and its very crowded almost full ( we make reservations 1 few days before)

They offer dim sum & ala carte .
The Peking duck with two ways eat is nice , meat alots in noodle.

The dim sum Cream of salted egg york bun is yummy , different from the normal buns outside, highly recommend.

Overall is good , can come and try out.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Good ambience and pretty good food. North siders should probably come visit this area in ORTO. #yishun
Was forced to order via online where online menu was limited and price did not reflect GST until payment. Paid 8 bucks for 6 meatballs with no pasta.
Portion was alright, good place for family dinner, lunch hours is not packed, but for dinner do call ahead to make booking

Poor delivery service  as when the food arrived to our doorstep it was already cold.

The delivery was supposed to come from 11.30 pm to 12.30 pm but it only came at 1pm without the full order as it lacked the condiments like the sauce and cucumbers for the peking duck ( had to wait for another hour for it).My daughter had to rush off to work without having a Father's day meal together with the family because of the late and incomplete delivery.

The quality of the food was subpar to the standards provided when dining in.Quantity of the peking duck was so much more lesser compared to the one we had when we dined in at your restaurant and the crackers lost their crispiness.

Overall disappointed with the delivery and not worth ordering delivery again for such big occassion as our Father day's lunch was ruined and everyone was left frustrated after this late delivery.
Went for dinner, nice restaurant, cheap and best. Taste is good. Worth for money
Good service.. great food

Some food nice some food not so nice.
The service okok but we were placed at a corner of the restaurant and the push cart didnt go to our side so we gotta wait very long to order our food. And you can only order your food via the push cart. I also dont know why the push cart didnt go around the restaurant systematically.

A hidden restaurant for tasty and value for money food.. The Nepali chicken Tash, Gumbo Soup, chicken momos, brownie with ice cream and house pour red wine was amazing. Genuinely reccomend this place..I think it‚Äôs underrated and deserves 10 stars.. service was great and warm too . I am coming back for sure ‚ò∫Ô∏è

2nd visit. Alacarte buffet
Nice food, good ambience and friendly staff. Recommended
Great baked pasta and the concept is very unique. Will visit again and recommended for everyone to try.

The only nice dish is the UNAGI Roll. Their fish is cooked perfectly, moist and seasoned lightly. The tonkatsu was dry and thin with a thick coating. The other sides dishes were average. However the price is on the high side even through there are at a secluded area.
One of the outlets that has lots of tables for groups of 5 and above. Not like Vivocity where they only have 1 table for groups of 5 and above.
Amazing food and also amazing ambience
5 star rating for a long standing restaurant, 3 decades. We set for a vegetarian meal, no regrets. Keep it up and will become my regular spot for Thai food.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: A tasty value meal. There is always people lining up for this Hawker stall.  The seafood Tom Yum is medium spicy, would prefer a it more spicy. Very good Thai noodle.  Fast service but some items are not available such as we wanted the mango salad.  This is recommended to us by a local friend and our opinion is: worth a try.

They are under Li Fang congee which I only found out when I saw their signboard. Like what many had mentioned, their pricing is more expensive. I still tried because their menu is quite interesting. The black chicken porridge is quite nourishing but annoying with the herbs hidden in the porridge, so go for others if you are not herbal fan. We paid like $30 for 2 pax. If you think of it as a meal at a restaurant then this price makes sense but if you wanna compare with hawker or coffeeshop then don't come. Overall we enjoyed our lunch there. üòä

Over hype is what I think after the meal
I had always seen long Q at PLQ, etc...
So during an off peak time, when I walk pass this branch at JP, I walked it. Ordered the set meal. short rib beef.
If you are not too hungry, this set meal will suit you. Everything front he meat portion (100g), rice, side dish is small. Note, meat shrinks when grilled.
Generally, you get a simple Japanese meal without smelling badly like BBQ after the visit.
Note, the condiment, garlic chili hits a different note..rather spicy.
Nice Tendonburi. Always feel good to dine in. Look forward to another meal here.
Pleasant dining experience with great service staff. Food selection is wide and the quality of food is passable.

The last time I visited Buddy Hoagies, the chicken was dry and hard. The ribs tasted like it was left from the previous night, very dry. That was almost two years ago, if I remember right.

I gave it another shot today. I head inside the restaurant half expecting the chicken being dry and hard again. I was greeted by friendly staffs. Nice.

I ordered the mixed grill that comes with a sausage, chicken and pork, served with coleslaw and onion rings. The set came with a drink and either a mushroom soup or minestrone soup. I chose the former.

The mushroom soup tasted bland. It‚Äôs white in colour. I do not know if it‚Äôs supposed to be that white. They serve a slice of soft bread with garlic spread. Nothing fancy.

The main course came before I could finish my soup. Fast. Too fast. I‚Äôm fine with it since I did not like the soup. This time round the chicken was moist. Thank goodness for that. The pork was smaller in size but tasted moist too. The coleslaw was not heavy on the sauce. Maybe if they give you a small wedge of lemon for your coleslaw would be nice. Anyway the onion rings were cold. If felt like the cook had made a basket of it and just left it there till someone orders it. Should have ordered the hot veggies instead.

Overall, pleasant experience especially the friendly staffs. Food wise, eerrrmmm, ok.

Noodle soup was good. The noodles is probably the highlight here. Unique texture - soft and slightly chewy..you can taste the separate strands.  I ordered the chicken noodle soup but requested a hot version which was available. The chicken pieces could be chopped more cleanly as I found bone fragments. The eatery is offering a free drink which each noodle soup ordered. Service was fast. No GST, service charge. Good service. Will try the noodle item which comes with 12 side dishes in future. Another favourite is the hot and sour glass noodles. Fave app offers a 10% discount on your next visit.
1st visit to Go Sushi at JP.. Sushi taste OK but the sushi not packed firmly, easily disintegrate when picking up with chopstick.. Unique way to serve food fast and fuss-free via shin train..

Decided to try Yakiniku-Go after trying their another competitor (hey yakiniku). The experience is quite similar except that it's slightly more pricier and the quality & taste of their meats are not as good. Overall an average experience.

Been eating at Sushi Tei since the late 1990s. Very sad to say, their standard has dropped.... the place didn't look too clean too. Many nice new sushi restaurants of better value and quality have sprung up all these years....
Delicious value for money great ingredients combination

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: This is my first negative review. The restaurant was completely different compared to a year ago. Good location, good food was completely ruined by bad customer service and cutleries used. It's really bad for the person who is taking our food order to move to other table abruptly while we are informing him our order. Cutleries quality of washing and the wash basin condition immediately has to be resolved to keep up the customers

Extremely rude & unpleasant staff. The plump woman manning the drink stall shouts at customers. The younger lady running the wanton mee stall is very rude too. Very impatient & frequently snaps at customers.
I wonder if the boss did not pay them salary on time? The staff there will simply spoil your day. Will never ever return again
Food is soooo good! They aren‚Äôt stingy with the toppings and you must especially try their cold noodles (it‚Äôs the best I‚Äôve had)

We were most pleasantly surprised at the quality, quantity and value of the food at this eatery.
A delicious fish, big enough for three persons with a hearty appetite, can be had for less than $20.
Would highly recommend Hong Fan to anyone looking for good mala fish or mala xiang guo at an unbeatable price! And by the way, service here is prompt and friendly too!

Interesting concept but quite pricey given that everything is self-service. Meat variations offered in menu was good but portion wasn‚Äôt enough for me even with 200g of meat. Most of the meat was mildly pre-seasoned but you can add more salt/pepper/others as you like, was delicious. Kimchi was interesting, had strong alcohol taste.

50mins dining timing but food took 15mins to be prepared, and I‚Äôm dining solo? Saw this piece of plastic among my meat and told the staff to tell their kitchen to be more careful, she went ‚Äúuh ya okay‚Äù her reply toward other customer was rather substandard too.

I gave 2 stars cause the salad was nice, the rest for this price you can pay a bit more and go for free flow.
Fantastic food and service. Good value for money
Have tried a lot of vegetarian dishes of shakuntals and it's really superrb

First up: if you're looking for this place, be sure to be look out for the Chinese signboard. Don't be looking for "Traditional Penang Food" in English now. It'll be a black signboard, with Chinese words in white. See my pic if you want to see what it looks like.

Secondly, note that my review is only for the chendol.

Is this chendol better than the one at Penang? I'd say definitively, no.

Ice: not finely shaved.

Noodles: nice green colour... No comments about colouring though, since I don't know what goes in there. But this is the brightest that I've seen of the chendols today (I reviewed Four Seasons Toa Payoh, and Dove Desserts earlier today). Unflavoured, which is disappointing.

Red beans: ahem if I want Penang chendol, I would be looking for those delightfully soft - and sweet! - kidney beans which I first tasted at Penang (and haven't found anywhere else since). You get a reasonable quantity of beans... But you should expect that, at $2.5, the most expensive of the chendols so far today.

Overall: nothing really strikes me about this chendol. It's middle of the road as far as I'm concerned... Or maybe I've taken too much chendol for today. I don't think so though. The gula melaka isn't generous, but you do get bits of it. The nice thing about it is it seems to come by default with *two* metal spoons, so in case you're sharing, you don't need to ask to one more. And the spoons are metal. An upgrade from the plastic ones that you get at Four Seasons, and Dove Desserts.
super nice chicken chop and pork chop. unbelievably tender! the auntie is damn fierce to the uncle who is cooking tho cause of the long queue üòÇ
Food is good. For the area and environment, it's a bit expensive
Visited on 16 Jul 2022, enjoyed the suculent NZ sirloin steak and nepalese chicken.. the dishes were done well and delicious

The new cai png stall is for risk takers. Ordering cai png here is like navigating a field of land mines. The promo during the first few days of opening will lead you to think that prices are cheap with no surprises, but things then changed. Meat that look like they‚Äôre cooked in a similar way can cost very different. A bit of canned mushrooms lingering in veggie dishes will make them cost the same as meat dishes. They don‚Äôt inform you when you order the dish. Simply misleading.

Curries never disappoint. The blend n balance of spices is spot on. The Prata & Naan r crispy but not oily, very more-ish. Briyani Lamb Shank curry is yumz!

2 issues we hd ytd - the fried fish was hard n not fresh and d makcik forgot our Teh C kosong.
Pls maintain yr standard n you will last a long time here.

I ordered roti john chicken with cheese on 27 July. Upon eating, I realized that they might had forgotten to add in cheese for my order. I approached the staff and asked him about it. He took a fork and poked on my food when I was eating halfway. It's so unethical and rude to do that to a customer. After that, he shouted loudly "What no cheese?" I was utterly disgusted by this behavior and I will not go back to patronize again. The old staffs before the renovation was so friendly and approachable.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: The food is good but it a spicy dishes of it. So remember to check with the staff if you do not want spice on your dish.

Decent Malaysian food from across the country all in one, convenient food court. Quality varies by stalls but some dishes like the Penang Char Kway Teow are quite close to the original‚Äôs. Portion sizes can be a little small for the price but still worth a visit if you‚Äôre craving for Malaysian food. Food court can be crowded and some dishes like the Hokkien Noodles can take a long time to prepare. Some patience required.

Not the best of location for wedding lunch/ dinner. The tables are packed together and staff kept asking guests to shift their chairs so they could squeeze through to serve food and top up drinks. Table planning/ positions could have been done better.

Utensils are sub standard. Almost spilled the soup due to the chipped/ broken bowl.

Food wise, it could be better. Glad that there is a  McDonald's on the ground floor.

Really nice family run restaurant, friendly place.

Quiet and unusual spot, located inside Omni theater, to the left of the entrance.

Food was rich and savory, delightfully crispy (yet soft) naan. Aloo Gobi was the dry version. Butter Chicken was amazing.

Must patronise!

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Slow service. Long waiting time nvm. Rude staff even worst.
Doesn't stick to scheduled closing hours, items often unavailable. Otherwise standard KFC fare.
Always great food served. Love their Food - and now they serve Abacus seeds as well üòäDelicious food!! üíï

Service :4 stars
Food: 3.5 stars
- the sausage veggie was too oily. You can see from the plate the abdundunt oil left.
-the kids beef burger is quite good though.
Value for money :4 stars

Ordered Claypot chicken rice via a delivery app.

Rice was fragrant with sesame oil. Taste-wise it was good. Salty and slight sweetness from the black sauce. Their chili is really spicy and slightly sour. I usually just mix it in together with the rice which adds an extra kick to the dish. For the ingredients, there were quite a few chunks of chicken but I didn't like that the skin was on as the skin was very chewy. There were also two small pieces of salted fish and only ONE miserable slice of my favourite Chinese sausage. *Sobs*
Well actually I have ordered this a few times and the amount of ingredients given are usually inconsistent.

Overall I do like their claypot chicken rice but I wished they were more consistent with the amount of ingredients in each order.

Nice ambience, good service
Nice mango pudding with mango bits inside, coconut milk on top goes really well

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Beancurd here is good! Gula Melaka was an interesting flavour to try but I preferred the original flavoured one. Hawker centre is clean, no birds flying in, toilets clean as well. Many food options here
Dimsum is delicious, price is reasonable and ambience of restaurant is good. It is juz 5mins walk from Tanjong Pagar Exit B.
Food was not very good. Staff did not seem very energetic that we were there.

I like the intention of this nasi lemak shop, where they make it affordable for anyone to have some good food. For $1, u get e egg and choose between ikan bilis or ikan kuning. For $1.50 u can get both e ikan bilis & ikan kuning. Then there are all the other addons. I loved the way they fried the chicken. Queue was not that long on a weekday late morning. Ladies at the shop are fast and efficient so it is best you have your order ready in your mind. Taste is not that strong as compared to other nasi lemak shops but my 4 star rating is for their nice intention actually.

First time trying since I was also nearby. Fan of Nasi Padang. But too expensive @ $6.50 , with only a small drumstick, spinach and a fried egg. Taste, to me, was normal. Some of the staff did not put on face mask or even wear mask properly also.
Awesome truffle chicken. One of the best Chinese restaurants to have a private wine dinner. My recent fave Chinese restaurant.

I first tried the pork chop from Ling Maison and thought the meat was tender. Sauce was a bit sweet for my liking but overall still nice. Took away the chicken chop for my mum who loved it as well. Look at that beautifully roasted skin! The following week, my parents went back for the salmon and chicken chop with pineapple. They absolutely loved it. I guess apart from the mains, what made ling maison stand out from other Western stalls in coffeeshop is their sides. They even have sous vide egg and red potato salad!

waited for 15minutes to eat (came at 5) and food was really goooood! highly recommend the soy garlic sauce + BBQ sauce combination! cheese fondue is yummy too :)

Have a good time, highly recommend u to try at least once in your life!

Terrible eatery! Ordered a Maggi Goreng that they asked if I wanted chicken or beef while neglecting to add that meat costed extra. Was served a dish of over cooked noodles that costed almost $9. Eat here at your own risk! Definitely do not recommend!!!
So tasty! Plenty of seats too. Good choice very nice service

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Very pleasantly surprised to have found this Nasi Padang spot here in this side of the country. It's very very popular, especially during lunch times. Good for small groups; try not to come in large groups expecting there to be seats. The ayam penyet is amazing. The nasi padang can be a little pricey, but that's nasi padang for you. Just point and choose what you want, then pay later. They have a system running. Just make sure you order the Ayam Penyet (smashed fried chicken)!
Ani was very nice and friendly towards me and my friends she made sure that we had a good time while eating
great service and offer new variety to all the school food!
Nice ambience and kind, proactive staffs. The peking duck and yam ring were delicious. We had a great meal.

Food (mains) here are good. Authentic filipino food. Desserts can be improved. Reason for my 1 star rating though is the service. (1) Experience from dinner some time back: We ordered mains (rice and sinigang) and desserts. The desserts were served first. I told the server that we‚Äôre having desserts after our meal. She was unhappy about that and said the desserts cannot be taken back to the kitchen and we should have told her earlier that we‚Äôre having the desserts after the meal. Uh okay? Isn‚Äôt that the normal sequence of a meal? (2) Experience from lunch today: We ordered 2 dishes with rice and drinks. Drinks, rice and 1 dish were served first. 15 minutes later, noticing that the next table who came after us got the same dish that we were missing, i followed up with the server. She checked with the kitchen and came back to inform us our dish will come after 15-20 minutes. No apologies whatsoever. Just informed us to wait. So to give her context of how long we have been waiting, I told her the table that came after us already got the same dish. At this point, the server blew up and raising her voice told me that if I wanted, she will take the dish from the other table and serve it to us.  Of course I said no. Before I could say anything else, she stalked off. From our table, I could hear her complaining loudly to another staff/ manager. Dish was finally served but the rice and the other dish had gotten cold already at this point. No one (no staff or manager) came to our table to explain or even just to understand what had happened. Originally, I let the first bad experience pass and gave them the benefit of the doubt but after today‚Äôs experience, it‚Äôs clear (at least to me) that the management need to be made aware of their staffs ‚Äòcustomer service‚Äô.

The pan-fried buns are really good! Better than the No Signboard chain.

The soup dumpling is lacking flavour though, especially when eaten with strong-flavoured noodles or other spicy dishes.
Authentic Sichuan Mala hotpot and grilled Fish. Value for money at $2.28 per 100 grams of food..Must visit if you missed Chengdu street food...
Economical Japanese food.

wrong item delivered,could not reach them on phone.
This the third time food panda delivered  wrong item or shortage of items
I like their xiao long bao than DTF
Great experience here! Delicious and affordable bowls. üòã

Been coming for quite a bit. The food is awesome and the service is superb. The outdoor dining ambience and decor makes me feel as if I'm in Phuket.
Do try the curry fish head... no regrets.
Highly recommended.
Value for money

Horrible service as there's no courtesy practice in this restaurant. They treated customer like a flog of hungry animals and reminded us that we are only given 50mins to finish up everything.

Especially a server named, Catherine, super rude!1

Not recommended for big group especially you have to seat few tables apart.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Went on a sat afternoon and it was quite busy but had many empty seats due to the rather large area. Feels like they might be a little short on staff with only 1-2 waiters that are always tending to someone, but still gets the job done rather quickly. Overall a rather satisfying meal, though the food is a little on the saltier side. Nice air conditioned cosy environment
Green curry with chicken is nice. Sweet and slightly spicy with a strong basil flavour. The coconut slushie is also good.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Very nice Teochew dishes! Portion is not very big. Prompt service and staff were helpful. We were given a private room and all utensils are available for us to self help. But the entrance of the restaurant can be confusing. Overall experience is not bad. Total damage for all dishes = $700+ as we ordered roasted pig. The lobster dish is not worth I feel as it was full of garlic. The rest of the dishes are good.

Taste was ok only but pricing on the very high side. Ordered 2 prata with eggs, 2 normal prata and 1 chicken Mutaba (total: $27+).
Delivered only 2 pratas with and without eggs and forgotten to prepare the Mutaba.
Sorry to say and I'll not patronage again

Nice place to have a meal, take extra precautions(be sure to observe 1m distance) as this stall seem to have long queues most of the times especially lunch/dinner, and there are many other stalls with good food, like chicken porridge stall, fresh brewed soya drink(omo)stall and Indian Rojak stall, thanks

Great discovery by my husband. Food is nice n Instagramable with very reasonable price. Since we dun eat beef, Waiter is friendly n helpful with great recommendation! Lamb n carpaccio with truffle is must try ! Satisfied dinner üòä
price a bit pricey but the taste is good...

I have just ordered this from grab delivery... Very disappointed with the food/per stick portion. And my food is mostly burned and bitter... I think most reviews here is either fake OR my order is done very badly.

I personally will not eat from their store in the future.

---------------------------
Responding to the owner's respond... Already said the order is burned and bitter...

Not sure, which part of my statements wasn't clear to you.

If I could give no star I wouldn‚Äôt want to give 1 star for this restaurant. Extremely poor service not worth your time to pay a visit. Ask the staff if we could sit inside, she rolled her eyes to us. Shout at us when we ask if paywave accepted or not.

Very fast and quick service.
The sambal is really good with a good spice in it.

San Bao Vegetarian
Vegetarian food here
food was really expensive and not tasty, not worth it even with burpple 1-for-1 üòÖ

Food average, abit pricy. The staff who is taking order is super unfriendly. I wanted to change my order, the staff stare at me, show me black face and said cannot change because they have prepared my order already but i waited for 30 minutes still have not get my food. Dont even deserve 1 star.

This is my second visit and I orfer the chicken meat ball pasta and the same taste amazing as always.Slightly better service by the staff will be better and will be much better if management can look into this.
Yes we understand the challenges in this industry but possible to have better staff with improved service to rock.the great concept.
All the best to zitimamas team

ordered oyster omelette and it took about 50 mins to come. when we asked the stall owner, he said he forgot about our order, and did not give an apology - not even a sorry or anything.
when we got our omelette after about 60 mins of waiting, we only managed to find 4 oysters inside. mind you my mother paid $6 for that omelette.
the stall owners were very rude the entire time and took everything for granted. ruined family night and wasted our time.
Cheapest n tasty nasir lema.Only $1.00

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: I got severe heartburn ‚ù§Ô∏è‚Äçüî• & acidity after eating here. The veg Biryani is probably the worst I had. Staff work like clueless. Slow in taking orders, a lot of confusion. Though my order was served early could see the annoyed faces of other people who ordered & kept waiting indefinitely.
Chicken that falls off the bone. Rich broth. Went with normal taste. Next time will try less taste. Finished the whole bowl, including the all the broth.

My Family tradition since young to celebrate occasions at this particular outlet. Family friendly experience is consistent thru the decades.

Though nowadays there many new fancy places that served steak, glad that Jack‚Äôs place standards manage to stood the test of time.

The prata has improved a lot with less oil..had poori with 2 different sides of potato and spicy pureed veg dish. But most important was the great service,attentiveness and the effort of the staff who greets all customers in English and with their goodnights...prompt service too.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Love the spicy and nutty dan dan noodles since the restaurant's days at Takashimaya.
Service is good. Food presentation is good! Recommend the sweet potato salad.
Very good pack of nasi lemak and epok epok. Only $1 each! They open very early so do come down earlier if you want to avoid the crowd.
Good food good time
Nice cosy outlet of popular local F&B  franchise and offers the full menu of items, served hot & fresh.
The most interested one is Waffles Ice Cream and Pizza.
Homely food options. Noodles like soba, ramen or rice bowls are available. Our dons came with miso soup.

Need a quick dinner so decided to settle it here. Used Burpple 1-for-1 deal so it is very affordable.

Ordered Katsu Chicken don and Tempura don. Each set came with a miso soup. Miso flavour is not very strong.

The tempura did not come with a dipping sauce which is a bit disappointing. Katsu Chicken was acceptable.

I dine here at least 3 times a week. I love the food. However, the staff aren't consistent with their serving. There are days the rice will be so much more and hardly any meat. Another time, their burrito can be pretty light.

Ordered Ramen, Soba tempura, udon tempura and mixed grilled skewers.
Service: Good but food prep/cooking was slow. waited almost 20-30 mins.
Quality: Ramen broth and dipping sauces (soba/udon) were watered down. Flavor lost already. Grilled skewers were okay. Salt/Pepper/Teriyaki sauce
Green tea and complimentary black coffee was satisfactory.
Price: 80$++ with tax
Verdict: Spend your money elsewhere

had the chicken chop which made rasa sayang western food famous.. comes with fries, baked beans, garlic bread, coleslaw on the side.. but the winner here is definitely the brown sauce... comforting food and value for money..

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
A limited number of stalls selling food.
The nice ones are the fried hokkien mee stall( tien tien lai) which is definitely a must try. There is also a stall selling teochew pau(teochew hand made pau), not too bad also. Not forgetting the famous fried carrot cake stall(chey sua), if you like your carrot cake that is crispy on the outside and soft in the inside, then you must try.

The food is amazing. My favourite items are the mee goreng, chapati, mysore mutton. But there are many other good dishes as well. The unique thing about this place is that the food really tastes like it's home-cooked, with love. Also very generous with the portions. Would highly recommend for events catering!

Very good Filipino food overall. Drinks on promo were affordable. I would come back again. I would love to see the service improve though. I hope the owner(s) are taking the steps to improve after seeing the other reviews here regarding the service.
One of the more famous snack brands in Singapore. Fun fact, most of their employees are senior citizens! Their food may not be special but their staff will certainly make you feel at home!

Absolutely no disappointment I can assure you as we been their regular all this while and each visit hasn't been a let-down with this vendor over the years.

ü¶ÜTheir signature Angelica Herbal Roasted Duck is a must to order for the meat eaters, it was simply savoury, meats were tender and juicy, flavourful  and simply gratifying it's worthwhile your calories believe me lolüòÖüòÖüòâüôÉ.

üå±The lettuce with oyster sauce were fresh and cruchcy stirred fried with fragranced wok hey (the charred after taste of the wok under high flames).

Sizzling hotplate beancurd with minced meat and Pickled Vegetables was delectable üòã.

It actually came with 2 rice but we ordered xtra YiFu Mee and it blended perfectly well with the roasted duck.

Home make Barley water was my favourite drink it's not too sweet and good to the taste.

I was at their branch at City Square Mall a month ago, i shall say that they were very consistent with their taste gastronomically, you don't see sub-standard throughout their outlets with my experienced. Kudos to the teams.

Damage was aroundüí≥ $62,  worthy for 2 pax.

Waitpersons were friendly and service was prompt, attentive and welcoming üòÅüòÅüòÅgood job!

It's lunch time and there's enough spaces between tables it can easily accommodate big group and its not rowdy and noisy here it's comfortable and relaxing.

Ambience was also hygienic, spacious and neat

Highly recommended if you are around.Try it NOWüòÅ

Sushi is not bad! I spent ard $20 (including taxes) ordered ard 6-7 plates of sushi. Minus one star bc for e new range of sushi that is supposed to have some butter on top of e salmon/scallop, the butter given was so tiny that I could not taste it. Otherwise e slices of salmon are fat enough for e price :)
It will be great also if their ice cream claw machine stocks some Meiji icecream instead also. (Understand that made in Japan ice-creams might be too expensive to maintain in the long run so even Taiwanese-made Meiji is much better than the dubious looking icecream inside)

First visit, reached there after 2pm. Well grill and flavourful. Would visit again.  üëçüèª

1

Nice food! Very old school western food, like those that were widely available in SG. Very similar to swensen‚Äôs. Good value for money, would recommend!

Nice environment for families, there is a little play corner to keep the little ones entertained.
Love their authentic Thai food by the Thai chef. Nice and neat place. Conveniently situated near TPY MRT. 1 minute walk
Nice roast duck noodles with crispy skin.. Favorite accompanied with sour and spicy thick soup. Usually quite packed during lunch, so good to visit earlier.

I hope the boss will read this. It will be my first & last visit for my family. Young Chinese lady service staff with black frame spectacle was extremely rude & impatient while taking our orders. No welcome greeting but remark like ‚ÄúI ALREADY SAID there is no other dessert except‚Ä¶.‚Äù. She looked agitated. How can one hear clearly if she mumbled behind her mask and standing a distance away?  Only repeat once and she can be so curt & rude. A polite crew would reply ‚Äúsorry our desserts are not available today.‚Äù When making payment, she didn‚Äôt smile nor say something nice, eg thank you, please come again. Pure transactional like a robot. You have lost a customer who is staying nearby & is a food panda regular. If you are not happy, you quit. Please don‚Äôt vent your frustration on your customer, who is supporting your business. The only choice for dessert was tapioca which tasted so hard. Worst I have ever eaten.
Flavourful and affordable zhi char food. Their fish soup is one of the better ones I have tasted. Mostly crowded though.

I always have a soft spot for Malaysian food BUT this is by far the WORSE dining experience for me! Very lousy staff attitude (like u owe them a living!) and naturally you will never get good food with a lousy cook! I've never post anything in social media but this lousy experience prompted me to warn others about this! If the boss even care enough about their business, they shd either train the staff or fire them all. Or maybe the boss is the problem, abused the staff and make them so unhappy. Whatever the cause, if you are looking for THE WORSE FOOD and THE WORSE ATTITUDE, u can definitely experience them here in the fullest form! I feel so disapointed with these unfortunate attitude when my memory of food providers in Malaysia are mostly warm and provide very good food! NOT HERE! have some pride please! Siakswei!üôÑüòí
Worth 1 time of expirence. Price is on high end for restaurant at neighbourhood area.

Best thosai I've had in a long while. Fast, fresh, and the sauces are really tasty too. However it can be a tad less salty.

Cleanliness can also be improved, there were leftover stains on the table where we sat. and air con was too cold

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Friendly staff and nice food.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Had to wait for very long because our order was apparently cancelled and the waiter did not inform us beforehand, instead she watched and did not say anything. We later on went on to ask and she only told us then, I felt that the customer service was bad because of the lady. Food overall was good tho. We came at 6 and received our first dish at 7+

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Had breakfast at the market on level 2. I tried the Hakka "thunder tea" rice and really liked it. Loads of veg and nuts mixed into brown rice with soup. All for $4. üëçüèº
Revamped from Tasha Restaurant to Semma Bistro. Good upgrade. The atmosphere is cool and food has a good variety. Recommended goto place. Sati soru (claypot rice)  mutton is a must try.
Cheap but average tasting food. Too much food color usage.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: Most of the sushi tasted decent. Unagi was however, not very fresh. It had a fishy taste. Chocolate cake was also too sweet for my liking. Not for fussy people. Staff was generous with the sauce. Cheap and value for money!

First time here, celebrated my parents‚Äô birthday. Ordered the steamed fish (900g), fresh & reasonably priced. üòã

Good service fr the staff, will return again. üòä highly recommend for family/birthday dinner.

Simple enbience. Food really above my expectation. Especially from Coffee Shop Zhi Char Stall. Service 4.8 out of 5 . The crabs are huge $68 per kilo That's the current price. Own by Mr. Lee. Quality of food and freshness are above standard. Worth my try to travel from Jurong to Ang Mo Kio.
Overall prices reasonable worth eating
Join as member you are entitled to 5% discount

Great portions for the price, was never disappointed with the meal,  enjoyed the minced pork / scallops / chicken / fish porridge that I've tried so far. Just wish there were more drink options than soybean. Still love the soybean and fried goodies that came with!
Good service and food overall. Unfortunately, half of the veg in the salad we got was baf and inedible. However we usually never have a problem with our orders üëçüèΩ
The pork chop used to be my favourite and had been visiting over the past 10 years, however recent visit was disappointing as the standard had dropped
$9 for 10 pan fried seafood mix pork dumpling and $3.50 for a small bowl of sour and spicy soup (before gst and tax) ‚Ä¶
Rubbish service. Forgot about our order and then made it the customer‚Äôs fault
As always, great food at affordable prices.

Very disappointed! It could be the Yishun brand is not up to normal sushi tei standards: very salty for every dish, the chef loss the taste or ‚Ä¶ ; curry rice the curry sauce is salty and artificial ‚Ä¶ seriously not a good experience.
Mee rebus is superb! though the gravy is a bit thick. Soto ayam we bought on Sat 14th Aug was without any chicken, strange.

I am not sure if the cook is having an off day but this was what came to me. It looked like the left overs of a meal. I was pretty disappointed. The soup was diluted, and the ingredients were so stingy. I asked for two portions of corn and got about 15 kernels. Would not come again.
Great outdoor dining, flowers overhanging the dining area. Powerful fan providing additional breeze. Order the grilled food and maki rolls.
Great experience. I ordered a vegetarian dish and it was tasty .

The place is clean and food preparation is quite fast.
Prata is crispy type but a bit small compared to normal stalls. Would need 3 pieces of 'kosong' to fill a meal... üòÇ
Tried with fish curry, no 'fishy' smell, spice not that overpowering... quite like it üòÄ
Food ordering feels a bit awkward blocking the narrow walkway at the entrance.

The female Indian cashier gave 12 X 10 cent coins in change when I bought something for 80 cents with a $2 note... And her drawer had packets of coins in bigger denominations.. she was simply lazy to open them!

Portions were a little smaller than expected from the pictures. But overall taste was pretty good.

Would recommend to give the soft shell crab a try!
Very yummy beehoon. Well fried. Truffle mushrooms were very tasty. Exquisite pork buns. Good service.

One of the best Msian style fishballs n fishcakes I have ever tried in Spore. Apparently made fresh daily, limited to 500 fishballs, till sold out.

Love the fiery sambal chilli sauce that goes with the fishballs, and the noodles are generously laden with crispy fried lard too. Prices have increased recently to $5.50/$4.50, big/small.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: First time here. Ordered jajangmyeon n Jjampong only as the 2 of us couldn't finish too much. Noodles are springy. Jajang sauce is just right, sweet but not overwhelming. Jjampong soup has alot of seafood freshness taste but as non spicy takers, we find it abit spicy but still find it very addictive. Overall, we considered them one of the best Jjampong n jajangmyeon in Singapore.
Today's twisty fries and nuggets was excellent, very crispy. 10/10
The seabass, glass noodle salad, pineapple fried rice is very nice.

A good place for a decent steak at decent prices. Ordered a medium rare steak n actually got medium rare. The black pepper sauce here is out of this world. It is thick, meaty, savoury, peppery and salty in a good way. Makes anything dip or slathered in it so yummy. Also like the light n fluffy round ping pong ball shaped thing served with the steak. Texture like a cake but goes well with the black pepper sauce

Nice and cosy place to dine with good air conditioning. Staff was polite and responsible but do note that, I was dining during off peak hours. The restaurant operates on staggered hours so please call to confirm and reservation maybe required for evening peak hour dining. Food pricing is definitely economical and affordable dining in such environment.
Not too bad, but price is on higher end.
Staff here are very nice and patient. Food was delicious.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The staff by the name Shidah, very friendly and excellent customer service. All the other team members are very welcoming and efficient!! Thank you suki thai toa payoh!!

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Samosa looks nice but a bit too cold wo warming up. Veg. food set the rice cold n selection limited. Pricept relatively higher than shami next dr. Will not visit again. Not impressef.
Worst meal ever! The Chicken was ice cold and the ÈÖ∏Ëæ£Á≤â was no where near anything I have eaten before (and I spent 17 years living in China)
Fantastic food! Had the mee rebus with babat(tripe) for $4.5. Gravy was flavourful and a generous portion size. Highly recommended. Be prepared to queue though!

Went for the ala carte buffet for CNY. Surprisingly, this style is not bad. Not all dishes are good tho but for the price it is. The jelly fish cold dish is my favorite. Char siew and the garlic slice pork are good. The chilli crab is surprisingly good. Meat are fresh n firm. The abalone soup is not bad. Not too salty. Overall value for price is there.
Wide variety of south Indian delicacies available. Prata is crispy and comes with fragrant fish curry. Must try.
Only takeaway, price wise rather steep! Compared to dine in. Do note that there is a price hike when you order via grab!

Queued about 30mins to get in, thankfully we got seats! Highly recommended to queue a lot more 2hours earlier before closing if you don‚Äôt want to stand in a long queue and ended up ordering take out cause last order is at 9.30pm. We ordered garlic naan, Gobi 65, chicken tandoori, buttermilk chicken and other dishes. They all were delicious and freshly made, the naan was so soft and fluffy, chicken tandoori isn‚Äôt tough or dry. Everything and services was great! Definitely worth the wait!

Very attentive staff. Outlet manager remembered me when I had some ice left in the middle of the chicken meatball ordered from previous visit. She was remembered me and offered a free portion of meatball but I decline as it is we were full. Takes feedback seriously and acts upon it

The concept reminded me of Genki Sushi. The variety is not comparable but in term of price and shorter waiting time I will vote for this restaurant. Their queue is so much shorter. I will recommend the black pepper series sushi and the fried prawn.
Love the Fry bee hoon! Delicious!

Really good food - have eaten multiple times and always appreciate the taste and quality.

Its understandable that the place gets quit crowded and the waiting time could get higher , however , being rude is definitely not appreciated. One of the ladies at the counter was quite arrogant towards us as we waited to get a take out for easily 60 mins over a 30 min wait time. At around 50 mins mark, whilst we enquired about the status - she was kind enough to rudely tell us - "want or not want - can cancel if not". Hey - we get it the food is great and stuff - however this is not the way to treat customers - at the end of the day - we are just asking and checking on the time after waiting at the restaurant for nearly an hour and probably we will wait more too - however , talking politely goes a long way in retaining customers.

Had the chicken chop. Being a chicken lover, this is one of the best I have had. Generous portion for less than $8, came with fries or mashed and garden salad or coleslaw. The meat was very tender and the black pepper sauce not oily or too salty. Must try, don‚Äôt come to Jackson Square just for noodleüòä
Although expensive but the food is tasty. I like their idly & chutney.
Fabulous food. Nice selection of sides
Came here at 10.30 but it was closed ‚Ä¶ üòû the opening time is misleading!

If you are craving for a taste of home cooked Indian curries that reminds you of all that youthful goodness, this is the place for you. Try the onion curry, salted fish curry and briyani. Ooolala. Suresh the owner and chef, also offers off menu items also that simply wows! Top notch and simply delish! Will definitely return. A quick word of caution about the super limited car park lots available in front of the shop.

Without recommendation from a friend, I would have missed this gem - that would have been awful. Located in the industrial corner of the Ang Mo Kio Estate , which mostly are a ghost town after office hours, Mad Charcoal chose to open the coffeeshop into the late (10pm, I heard). Some standard dishes and the other items were created to what the freshest the market has to offer that day - which will please all crowd that chose to slow down for the night. When I first visited, i saw only a few customers, on a Saturday night!! From dismay, the mood swing quickly to a gastronomic excitement. Value-worth European Gourmet had us convinced, and we are sure that, most if not all blind-tested connoisseur  would place the gourmet to be from a posh restaurant. We were back another 2 days later with our child - it is that good. Now go try.

My to go order was missed and I ended up waiting for 20 mins. The person packing the food was right in front of me and didn't bother to enquire about my order number but instead avoided looking up at all. Only when I asked then they realized the miss but tried to avoid acknowledging it by saying they will start preparing it...which took 2 mins to be ready.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Decided to try out this Chinese restaurant on a weekend because there was a long queue at the Thai boat noodle store and I had a pleasant dining experience here. ORTO has been one of the few places I was recommended to go to that changed my perception of the North and the place itself has a nice view to boot. I love the fact that you can dine either indoors or alfresco depending on your mood and the food at Tasty Loong didn't disappoint. It was just unfortunate there was only the 2 of us so you guessed it, the more people the merrier as that means you get to savour more dishes. Their pumpkin noodles was their signature dish and it's a popular one but I felt it was nothing much to shout about. However their braised pork belly was good and certainly a dish I would order again! I have yet to try their roast chicken but judging by the no of the same dish sent to various tables, it must be popular too. Can't wait to head back there and try their dim sum menu too!

This is my first time here and I felt like I have stepped into an authentic Chinese Teahouse in Hong Kong. TungLok Teahouse @tunglokgroup is located at Square 2 which is nicely set against a backdrop of a busy Hong Kong Street. The concept is to re-create the convivial atmosphere where families can gather together while chatting over hearty dim sum delights.
.
TungLok Teahouse is also the first Chinese restaurant to launch the automated tray delivery system. Basically, once your order is ready, the food will arrive via the delivery track that is beside your table. You will pick up the food from the delivery track and you had to press the red button to have the tray return to the kitchen.
.
The menu features an array of exquisite handmade dim sum selections as well as Chinese favourites and Teochew cuisine

the food is really worth it. portion is very big and it's not too expensive. The soup and garlic bread is not the best but everything else is really good for the price. I would really recommend the ribs.
Good food

Second time here and the food is consistent as usual. Price steeper than usual, which is to be expected across the outlets.
Technology update: you can scan the qr code at the entrance to get the q number. Can be busy during lunch/dinner times. Be sure to come early.
One of my fav Cantonese restaurant to go to,  pity they have left with the last branch at Maxwell now. Go support them üëç

Great food at decent prices.

Service was also great, the waitress told us that the quantity we wanted to order was too much for 2 people which was very appreciated

Not the easiest place to get to, but it‚Äôs nice and quiet. Hope it stays around for a long time!
Food is very nice. And fast!! Dont have to wait so long for the food!!

Ordered a voucher on fave for a 7 course meal that included cold starter, shark's fin soup, cod, prawns, abalone, Ee Fu  noodles and mango pomelo sago dessert. The dishes were distinctively tasty, with the cod being very generous as well as the sharks fin. Prawns were well cooked in a unique sauce that we all enjoyed. We definitely hope to be back
Delicious food with superb service! Definately coming back again!

Waited for more than 30mins for the food. Taste of the food so so. Price reasonable. The fried dry tofu not nice, fried rice only egg and spring onion, fish so so.. shui jia too soft.. staff very friendly.

Zingerito okok only lah. Not cheesy enough. Service still as slow as ever.

Standard KFC food. Food generally is ok but the waiting for your food to come need to take quite some time. Not sure are they lacking staff or what...
The meal I had anyway is so freaking full lol. Only thing to improve is service I guess.

A place for some home cooked inspire meal. Service is good but a bit slow due to staff strength. Curry beef with prata & chicken rendang nasi lemak taste good. Burbor chacha taste nice but all the sago stuck into 1 lump. Chendol too sweet without taste of coconut milk.
Excellent Malay food
Good and helpful staff make your day with them.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: bought here few times before all staff given enough for the soy sauce and wasabi, but this time served by cashier name hoo rae en have limit for the soy sauce even request,unlike
Yet to try heard that their rating was good.

A little "expensive" for the portion you're getting. Food tastes okay. Quesadilla had very little cheese which was quite disappointing. The fries were fresh though (which I really liked). The Churros were quite good but nothing special about it.

Didn't really think the food here would be that good but I was pleasantly surprised!

Price isn't too crazy on par with typical Chinese seafood shops, but the quality is on point.

I truly enjoyed some of their dishes, namely the mee goreng, Sambal Kang Kong, Cereal Prawns and even the fried rice! Nice big portions and well worth the amount that you pay.

I would highly recommend this place if you are in the neighborhood, or you can get it on Grab/Deliveroo/Foodpanda as well.

Beverage stall opened by young entrepreneurs. Worth a support! They accept paynow. They offer rare drinks like butterfly pea but the highlight is the Thai iced milk tea with a hinge of coconut taste. According to them their specialty is their coconut coffee.
Food is good

(Translated by Google) There is one very fierce! Chinese woman with bad service attitude! Spend money on things like you owe him money! Was a very bad experience! üò°üò°
