Delicious food .  Large portion of rice being served  , so you dont have to ask for  extra rice . Friendly lady staff asked - whether we need  extra soup or not ?  I Said ,‚ÄùNo‚Äùat the beginning but end up  finishing  all and have to  request again . Fish soup was full of Flavour üëåüëå.
ordered from grab a saba fish & beef rice but only received the rice & beef.

The two Chinese ladies are so rude, so impatient! The one at the cashier, I gave her $10 for $2.40 meehoon set, she gave me back $2.60. I stunned for a while before mastering courage to ask her nicely, eh how much is the meehoon...she straight away replied me you gave me $5 right? The answer is like giving her away. She then threw $5 on the counter for me. They need to be fired!!

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Fantastic spice and loved the ginger + pork soup
Delicious Dim Sum and alot of others ala carte local dishes!
Great briyani sold here. Chicken rice and other  malay stall also not bad. The only issue here is, need to wait very long for drinks that have been ordered.

A hidden "pot" in Duxton. Chinese food with a little twist in a black gold theme restaurant.

Food portion is decent. Taste ok. Friendly staff too.

Thank you to Sandrine for the attentive service.
Food was quite good. We had Oyagu Don and Gyudon. I wouldn‚Äôt mind coming back a second time.
Ordered the Ê∞¥ÁÖÆÁâõ and ÈÖ∏ËèúÈ±º via foodpanda. Wife felt the latter was "fishy" but perfectly fine for me. Beef could be more tender but the taste for both was really good. Will return for sure.
Satisfied

My favourite dishes : Coffee Pork Ribs and Jing Long Chai. 5 stars for these 2 dishes.

A non air-conditioned food court in an industrial park but never felt warm or stuffy here.

Overall 4 stars because they often forget to serve us our food when it is crowded and need to keep reminding them. Happened a few times for the many times we dined there.

But will still go again and again.
Thairu sooru is nice and maggie goreng is gd..

For 1 dollar a stick.
It's pretty decent. Would love if they added more seasoning. Can't really compare to Johor standard but it's good enuf if you have a craving.
Theres Thai milk tea from the drink stall and mookata near by too. Overall a good place to chill and eat

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Nothing really fantastic in my opinion. I tried Set A with fried dumpling, sweet sour pork, black bean sauce noodles and seafood soup noodles. Dumpling is quite tasty but overall I feel that the food is only average. Service is still good. Price is on the high side. Sweet sour pork smallest is $28. Wanted to try jelly fish salad but it‚Äôs $38. In my opinion only worth going once to try, unlikely to return again.

Food is ok, the wait is bad.
Not sure if they forgot our order. First few orders came about 10-15mins. Our handrolls however took more than 30mins, asked the waiter to check for us, came back saying the chef will make for us NOW?

THEN our orders came 5-10mins later. Then we noticed the people who came in later than us have handroll orders go to them first.

So is the system not working properly? Or did they forget our orders? Highly doubt I'll be going back again.

Not worth the wait at all. Highly NOT recommended

Oh man, this is seriously yummy and super worth travelling down to an industrial area for. Love the smoky flavours, tender meats, big portions, and superb seasoning. Price is very reasonable.

The P1 platter is to die for: it has pork, beef and chicken, and the interesting chili sauce goes well with the meats (very spicy though so don't dip too much lol).

As for the sides, the ratatouille was rather average but still hearty, and the garlic fries were good enough even without dipping into sauces.

We're planning to go down again or order delivery for house dinner parties next time.
Good food and service, quiet and nice ambience.

Was thinking this is a zicha place but didn't expect it to be a Chinese restaurant. And parking is super horrible here so please come here in public transport. Unless you're willing to pay for valet which is wth .... lol

But that aside, food is super good!! Every dish hits the spot, esp the yam ring, fried garlic pork and duck!!
Don is really nice but rice was a bit undercooked
Good place for kitchen training

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Was happening to view my archive picture and decided to post about this.
First of all, queue is long. Waiting time is long. Staff on duty was kind of rude
When it‚Äôs my turn, the auntie was communicating with me in other language Cantonese and Chi? Ask what is she promoting me for the new dish, she reply in Cantonese which I don‚Äôt uds. I tot why not just try lo.

End up I‚Äôm getting 1 slice of abalone that cost me $10. Really not worth the try
Tasty but not the place to go to if you're looking for grilled

Last ate here few years before Covid-19. Chanced again upon this place while collecting something from the office space here. Totally amazed by their beef brisket and pork belly, their sides also is really worth it as we ordered aglio olio pasta! Owner was also super pleasant and polite, had really good vibes here with good prices too! Will come again :)
The rojak and the gravy is really delicious. They give you a good amount of gravy. Do take note that there is a 10 cents charge for an extra glass if you want to share your coffee.

My dear Malaysian friend recommended this place for authentic Ipoh food. Price is very reasonable. Similar to foodcourt or kopitiam price. Their signature cheecheongfun is a must try. Very üëç Curry noodle is üòã too. The spring onion cheecheongfun taste ordinary, can skip that

Che' Rose Nasi Padang has been around for over 40 years.Che Rose Nasi Padang  is renowed for its Padang dishes and best customer service.One of the best stall we can find in Singapore. Its authenticity padang recipe makes many customers comes back again and again.

You won't be dissappointed when you come here to experience what Padang food all about. I don't have to go into details about, but you will find their food up to your  satisfactory.

So if you crave of Nasi Padang come to Che Rose Nasi Padang at Blk 128 Lorong 1 Toa Payoh.
Average Japanese food, something that you might find in a food court. The rice was dry and not the short grain type you would expect.
Food was ok, would prefer it to be more flavorful. Service was very good.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Not wanting to give a one star rating due to its facility being well ventilated and clean but the service must improve in order to prevent a future incident happening.

1) burner cooks slow that my table was seated for 3 hours in there.

2) we ordered buffet set but because we sat for 3 hours we could not order any more than we wanted.

3) we asked for another set of burner but was declined to unknown reasons.

4) we asked if we could change the buffet set to ala-carte but was also rejected as it was too late to do so?

5) we had 3 people sharing 1 burner but we spent 3 hours in there but did not even finish cooking our one and only order of meat.

6) if the Thomson outlet could change my ala-carte order to buffet because of their technical issues im sure the toa payoh outlet could do so too.

7) i spent $104 for 3 people ordering only $50+ worth of meat.

This is unfair as we could not order anything more due to the time and also the burner not being able to cook fast nor being able to open a new burner due to the manager saying so.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
V tasty chicken rice, char siew a bit tough and a tad sweet.  Soup very tasty with lots of ingredients too.
Place very crowded and noisy.  Have to come early.... to queue.  Will definitely come again

cheong fun is too dry. Asam laksa & nasi lemak are okay. Rojak is nice.
But this outlet is quite far from bus stops which is 10mins walking distance.

Most people there are having Malacca Lok Lok/steam boat. I went there specifically for the Hokkien mee and prawn mee. Prawn mee stock was really rich, unlike most places. It‚Äôs an aircon coffee shop with friendly staff.

Food is good. But owner attitude is bad. Tartar sauce diluted but still gave little then ask for more. Said need charged $1 when is so watery. Then some buyers haven't claim their food. The owner shouted say who buzzer keep beeping come and collected in a very rude attitude. Nice food but bad attitude. Just caz biz good doesn't mean should be cocky.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Bought 5 packets with mixture of duck, roasted pork, char siew, chinese sausage & 1 egg with rice but egg missing. Taste still can make it but the quality of the char siew is like giving me the whole fats. Meat is 5-10% but the fats is 90-95%. Duck meat is also more on bone than meat. Suggest not to tabao (packet) but eat there otherwise more will be missing like my egg. Rice is just plain rice not using chicken rice. Please patron the stall to confirm my reviews.
Not bad as usual. Too bad the coffeeshop is too far away in the corner.

Do not go for the dim sum buffet. Web stated 3-5pm, 430pm the staff will chased all the customer away. A lot of item is not in the buffet. All staff very rude, attitude in services. Worst restaurant I ever been.

3rd time went to Collin's, my hb like de food & ambience there, we went there for my hb birthday celebrations, coincidentally they hv Xmas set offer, really worth the price, till now he still missed his bday meal... üòÖü§≠
Service is good but shoyu taste not really used to theirs. Salmon sashimi not fresh enough. Might consider to return but at the moment got better options nearby.

Very accommodating people work here. I like that they do try their best to Ensure we have a good time even in this trying period. The food is quite well prepared and I am surprised at the speed. Pizza size is smaller than outside so do order 2 if you are planning to share. Lamb shank is very well done - loved it. The Beef tenderloin is okay for the price that I am paying but the black pepper sauce is too over powering. Chicken with pork ribs is disappointing but chicken is well marinated.

An excellent Thai restaurant with an equally efficient staff.
Real authentic Thai food at a reasonable price.
Food quality was fresh & great .
Montark service was prompt & she would explain the menu to the uninitiated explaining how the dish is cooked.
I would highly recommend this place üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

Nasi Lemak. A ubiquitous dish easily found all around our island! Easy to find, but to get something really good, not all that easy!
Selera Rasa Nasi Lemak. It's hands-down our family's favourite coconut-infused meal. No attention is sacrificed to detail. The rice; bryani, cooked with coconut milk. This gives the Nasi that beady-rice appearance which doesn't clump together when served. Bryani itself already has an aromatic smell on its own, so infused with coconut milk, brings the flavour and aroma to a whole new level altogether!

Those wings! Amazingly crispy! We love just how our meal is accompanied by the 'music' of crackly sounds whenever somebody bites into their chicken wing! The seasoning permeates into the meat, moist and steamy-soft layers that follow the crispy outsides!

And what is Nasi Lemak without its sambal? The sambal used here is sweet and tangy, with hints of onion-sweetness, and paired with their already flavourful rice, makes for a meal befitting a Tuan:)

Worth visiting if you are looking for Chinese food in Jalan Kayu area. Visited on Friday evening. Quite packed around 7pm and seems to be short of experienced server. We were seated inside and situation was sort of chaotic as the service staffs seems very disoriented but they are doing their best to serve.

Food came out of kitchen at a fast speed. Taste wise is good. Of all the dishes ordered (sorry not all had pictures), we only find curry fish head gravy a bit watery and Mongolia pork ribs not to our expectation. The rest of dishes were good. Especially the homemade tofu and hand shredded cabbage are very nice.

They had local food and also SiChuan dishes. Saw a lot of others ordering grill fish. Will want to try in next visit! And hoped that their service staffs are better trained up by then.

Great value, big portions. Wish it was more juicy though.

We came around 3pm on a weekday. Ordered a platter that came with bbqed180gm-ish beef brisket, chicken chop thigh and two slabs of pork ribs.

Chicken and ribs were a little too dry. But love the brisket. Felt they were pre-cooked and reheated though.

Good thing they came with refreshly made bigass sides! Carbonara as sides!! House salad was tasty too.

All this for 26$ that feeds 2-3pax!
Tasteless Assam Laksa @ SDG5.50 and it‚Äôs not even sour at all. The ingredients are also pretty pathetic‚Ä¶ might as well go for D‚ÄôLaksa which is cheaper and nice. Disappointed!
Overall their food is excellent the only part is they use Low quality rice instead of Thai rice which I feel they should as it‚Äôs Thai food. I hope they can improve on their rice quality

Went in the morning to try their nasi Padang and it definitely deserves 5 stars. Food was delicious, portion was perfect and best part was the affordable price! The staff there was really friendly too!! Have yet to try their noodle section; looks really good too!!
Food not fresh. Meat very hard teeth also want to drop. Ask for another pkt of chilli owner face turn black.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Good service. Tasty food. Will always go to the nearest Nandhana‚Äôs whenever I crave Indian food

Stumbled upon this shop on a rainy day and we were pleasantly surprised! Service was great, and zamzi recommended a great bottle of sake to go with the food.

Food was tasty and prices were reasonable! We ordered otoro handrolls and they were pretty generous with the ingredients. Ordered the beef bowl and the Australian striploin beef and rice was well seasoned. Also ordered the ika and we absolutely loved the combination of seasoning + sauce!

Overall the food and service really made an impression on us and we really enjoyed it! We will definitely be back for more :))

Had the lunch promotion spicy ramen but did not enjoy it. Ramen noodles are quite too soft and vegetables were spinach that didn't felt like they matched. The lunch set came with a drink, salad & oranges. Soup broth was so-so, nothing really "ramen" about it.
Overall, I felt that the taste and presentation is quite comparable to what you can find in food courts - which made my lunch set not worth @ $12.90++.

Went there for idly (9.30 am) and it was sold out. Ate rava dosa and vadai which were simple and good enough.
The place is within a food court and it is near the Sri Arulmigu Murugan Temple.

Food is delicious and price is very reasonable. 5 of us and less then $100. They offer us a free dish tat taste like shrimp roll & free sweet potato soup. I love the Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ which is awesome. The stuffed toufu in Claypot is quite large so it takes up most of our stomach space!

Tried to purchase some food from them but I assumed I went a bit late at about 4.45pm and their other items were sold out except a little balance for Satay. Maybe would try some other time. But I noticed that their not too customer's friendly or maybe they're worn out for the day!

Visited this place for a late supper with a a couple of friends. They served pretty good prata and they made them fresh.

Curry was thick and tasty. The only drawback was the price. Very expensive in terms of prata.

The best thing about this restaurant is the staff's service.  I've always experienced good service from the staff at Jack's Place AMK when dining in, or taking away.  I hope the management takes note of this and keep their staff in these difficult times.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: The food here was amazing and filled me with such warmth. We tried the teh halia, cheese naan, chickpea masala and mutton briyani. It was an authentic experience and my family and I really enjoyed the food. 10/10. Would love to return again. We left the store very satisfied and happy.
Affordable price. Green Rice taste good, Ikan Bilis good. Chix wings not bad, bagedel good and the sambal is nice but could a be abit more spicy. Overall I like it.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
It's rare to find good food with good service here in Singapore.This stall is one of the rare gems.

On service,the staff was very patient in explaining to me the differences between the 3 types of grilled chicken,and took the trouble to double confirm my orders.

Speaking of food quality,this is so far the best grilled chicken I had in Singapore.The outside is a bit charred and crispy,while the inside is tender and juicy.When you try to extract the flesh,it comes off easily.Only priced at $4.50 (for chicken only),which is very reasonable,considering the effort put in and the quality.

The Nasi Lemak was full of coconut flavor.Not the typical type you find here,which only has a hint of coconut flavor.It is comparable to Boon Lay Power Nasi Lemak,which in my opinion is one of the best in Singapore.

It was well worth my effort travelling up all the way just to try it.But what really attracted me to give the stall a try was the owner's sincere gesture in handling the complaint made by a customer.

We usually see owners or customer service officers responding with an apology,which is all.But this stall owner was willing to offer the customer a free meal,I think action speaks louder than words and I applaud such an act.

One final point: I don't take egg.I told the staff that I wanted my set without egg,and she immediately told me that I could change the egg to something else.I was impressed.

Most of the time,if I said I didn't want something,that was it,no replacement,and the amount of food given is the same,price is also the same.I would say this stall is very ethical in its business operation.Thumbs up and may your business prosper.

Rebranded from the one that originally located at CQ Central. It might be my failing memory but had thought the taste was not up to mark after relocating to novena. While it tastes great (and sticky), the tangsuyuk had a lot of bites. But at least it reminded us to chew well before swallowing. Jjajungmyun will feed you well and at $11++ per bowl, it's probably the cheapest from a restaurant. The dumplings are a hit or miss with a price tag of $10++ for 13 bite-sized ones.

Absolutely love the black bean noodles and sweet and sour pork, can really taste the authencity! The portion for the set meal is great and really worth the money. Service staff were nice! Food was served promptly! Will visit againüëç Thank you!
Cheap and best restaurant. One of my fav around amk.

They have put in effort in making their menu interesting with fun description and nice photos for their dishes that appeals to the palate.

The interor decoration of the restaurant is acceptable.

We are not impressed with the 2 dishes we have ordered. The butter abalone mushroom is nicely fried and crispy, however its too sweet and we do not like it marinated with curry. The ma po to fu is Sichuan Style with a very strong mala taste. We had mo po to fu from other restaurants which is more fragrant and less spicy.
Good food , cheap food and good staff's

Tried the curry pig skin ccf. As a Ipoh Kia myself, the ccf is indeed very smooth and soft in texture , one the few best. But the curry is not thick enough and lack of flavour , also can't taste curry flavour from the pig skin (by right the pig skin itself should be flavourful enough). The long bean also a bit hard and raw. Can try if you are nearby but don't set your expectation too high

I was disappointed with the quality served at Jurong Safra branch. Only 3 service crews on that day, beside the slow service, the food quality was bad, steak was tough, lobster was over cooked and not fresh.
These 2 stars was given for the 3 service crews as they are trying their best to serve everyone.
I have pics to contribute as I really have no mood by the time food we're served üòü
Quality food at reasonable prices. Service was fast and excellent, highly recommended to eat here. Value for money.

Great Thai food. All the flavors are spot on. Fairly priced, delicious, and such friendly and accommodating staff. Highly recommend. Try the papaya salad, pork cheek, tom yum, heck - everything is great. Love the oyster and Prosecco for $11 on Friday. Super promo.
Great experience dining experience! Peking Duck was cooked to perfection, the meat was succulent with a natural sweet aftertaste! Customer service was top notched too! Will definitely be back again.

Well a variety of delicacies to feast here. Though one may find it pretty expensive compared to other eateries, its worth the price one pays as the dishes are tasty and delightful. Its worth every penny spent. Friendly staff and a cosy atmosphere dwells in the dining area.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Ordered 5 egg with fish curry and 5 plain with dhal curry but was rejected.Why?because they just don't wish to give even if i can pay extra.Its not bout how nice the food is if the service is this way!Last time when just open,they are not these arrogant.Remember even if customer not always right but atleast differentiate when and when to appreciate them.DISSAPOINTING!
Great place for small snack. Fried Gyoza is my favourite! It's has outlet all around in Singapore.
Interesting fusion food. They are really generous in giving food freebies. Portion is huge and one main would be good for two pax, unless you‚Äôre really hungry.

Ordered the popcorn chicken with rice. Requested to remove coleslaw and the stall owner gave even more popcorn chicken! Wow.

The chicken is crunchy and spicy. Extremely satisfying.

Rice is flavourful too. Goes quite well with the chicken.

Very generous serving.

Awesome bihun soto! Added a big fat bergedel as well and it was great! Place seems to be very popular! A lot of people had pre-ordered their satay as well! Stall owners were very friendly folks! Would definitely return to try the mee rebus!

Tried the Nepali food again this 2nd time that I went. The last time I was there was about 7-8 years ago and I had the sherpa noodles. It's no longer on the menu but this time, I shared 2 of the Nepali dishes - the lamb and chicken with rice - with 2 friends and the pakora (?). They were all delicious. Pakora was piping hot and crispy when it arrived, and all snapped up by our table of 5 immediately. The lamb was so flavourful that I can't wait to have it again the next time I go. The chicken was good, too, but I prefer the lamb. Only downer was the yuzu drink that tasted like it had too little yuzu.

The staff was very friendly and helpful as well. Went there on a crowded Friday evening, but food still came fairly fast. Hope to be back again soon with my family.
Everyone should try ,
nice and delicious food. highly recommendedÔºÅgood customer serviceÔºÅ

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
Love the food here, must go hawker center for local delicacy esp Hokkien mee (best of the best) many snacks and desserts
Yet to try the muffin and you tiao

Minus 2* for the tables and hygiene
People could be ignorant and forget to wipe down tables after eating especially on busy period like weekends *sigh*

(Translated by Google) Recently opened. fruit juice. Can't eat all cold
Only the juice will burn. I have been substituting for just a week.
Please don't understand if you can. Recklessly

Nice food. Nice place but alittle oily while dine in.

Food quality and portion was great as always. However, the crowd that weekend was bustling and that made the main course arrived late, an hour late to be exact. Ambience was nice, staff service was tip top, they always try to accommodate requests at their best. Location-wise, not that easy to get to but you can drive or take a Grab down. It's located not too far off the Newton Food Centre.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Lots of choices to choose from. Queue move fast. Love their beef rendang.

My honest review was deleted. Went here to have dinner with my family. Last visit was bad. Returned after 1 year hoping that they imlroved. It was the weekend but totally empty. Shows that the bad quality remains. Food is super salty. Service is so-so. No service staff on the floor. All hiding inside.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Didn't know expect to have authentic Sichuan food from crystal jade. Highly recommend the Chong Qing Pickled Mustard Grilled Fish and the Chong Qing La Mian. Shiok! The sweet potato pastry is not too sweet.
Best plain tosei with side potatoes.. thanks

The Mini karanegi chashu Don is extremely salty, feedback to the crew however claim it‚Äôs normal. That‚Äôs ridiculous! Seem like not listening to my feedback seriously. I will just accept the outcome and blacklist the restaurant. Everyone out there if u lack of salt or low blood pressure u can opt for it.
Good and authentic Thais food at a reasonable price. Had the Phad Thai and Tom yum soup. Both are good. Will go back again.
Broth is thick and nice.. will come back again

Excellent food! Menu is extensive and seasonal to a particularly high standard of Halal Donburi. Definitely fine dining bought into hawker centre atmosphere üòÇ It can be expensive but worth it and they do different deals on different delivery platform and they even have Burpple (1-for-1). I have purchased from them through Foodpanda and they got like 50% OFF so it‚Äôs worth checking them out before you order your donburi. You could save alot! Highly recommended.

Delicious! I love the chicken with the creamy sauce and pork belly, the sausage too. I was shocked with the "side dishes" as it is like a 1 meal already like the pasta. Will definitely come back again. Highly recommended!

This is my fourth time here.The previous 3 times I was here and they were sold out. Queued for half and hour before it was my turn. Order the $5SGD portion but unfortunately they ran out of fishcake. Have to say the homemade fishball was really nice.noodle was delicious but was a little dry. Instead of the usual chill sauce for the noodle, they added something that looks like a dry chilli paste. for those who wish to try, strongly recommend you to come before 11am.

Food has dropped the standard, service very bad. At times they even bother if u call them, plastic spoon given to wat puri. Not sure ,how their thought process on intake of food, one of the aunty sound quite rude, when I asked for spoon, then my drink was not served yet till I finished 1 puri. Disappointed!!! No more going there üòÄ

$4.80 for mee rubus + chopped chicken chunks + satay sauce. I like the taste. Not  overly rich and doesn't make you feel jelak even towards the end. Generous portion of chicken. Even though its breast meat, it was not dry. Will definitely eat again.

The comments only for their ala carte buffet.
1st the planning of siting is very bad as the place is big but alot of empty table in between so the server had to run the whole place to send the food , even worst can see that they are under staff.

2nd Waited 20min before they take in our order .After our 1st order , waited another 25 min before 1st dish was serve. Then was told that the signature items they forget to key in n had to wait again....

3rd Beside their signature items all other dish was serve cold (room temperature food plus in Aircon room). Really feel that the Zi char in coffee shop will taste better than most of the food .

Lastly can see alot of ppl was complaining and there was 2 table that left eating halfway saying that they will still paid . (Had been waiting for more than an hour and only 1/3 of their food serve.

Btw this was on the 1st of Jan Saturday dinner.

Rasa Sayang has a special place in my heart as a food stall serving Western food in Ang Mo Kio. One of my favourite places for Western food in Ang Mo Kio. I like the salmon fish it serves. The popular dishes here with most people are: Chicken Cutlet, Chicken Chop, the Chilled Ribeye Streak. Non-aircon coffeeshop environment.

Tasty soup, handmade fb & fish cakes. Not too salty, meepok texture is alittle soft. Pork lard & fried onion done superbly. Kind of like yong tau foo savoury version. 4.5 stars- Perfect for daily. Will be back!
Restaurant renovate with more variety of menu and good ambience . Much changes from last time . Good service and tasty food ..
Was there for lunch. Good and fast service. Staff was friendly and food was delicious. Mainly western Italian food.
Cosy place but pricing can be cheaper for such a place....

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content:
Firstly, I was really excited when there‚Äôs gonna be one outlet opening at Toa Payoh HDB Hub area.I got sushi from them last week and this week. Both visits were during lunch time.

However, on my second visit, the quality of service by the cashier was disappointing compared to the first time I visited.
The cashier during my first visit gave me chopsticks and the cashier for my second visit says it‚Äôs $0.20 for chopsticks which is reasonable but I didn‚Äôt get it.

The cashier did not finish my transaction before moving on to attend to the grab orders. The transaction took a little long. I think the quality of service could have been improved or they could have better manage their manpower in this outlet.

Above is my experience and I still enjoy their sushi, I just hope  to have a better experience the next time. Thank you.
Garlic Naan, Mee Goreng Pattaya and the Beef Briyani were really great. Family loves it, 2nd time having it üëçüèªüëçüèª
Previously ordered chicken chop fried rice, didn't expect to be served chicken pops fried rice instead. Rating could've gone lower if it wasn't for the decent fried rice.

Food was alright, not stunning. I got a hotpot with beef and the beef tasted great, although there could've been a bit more soup. Also, remember to check your receipt - I was charged for something I didn't order and paid about $7 more than I should have. The service staff (an uncle) was very nice though!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
We have eaten here many times over the years. They have good days and bad days.

Tonight's food was excellent, but possibly because dining in was disallowed, so the chef has time to cook slowly.

The Prawn Paste Chicken were very crispy, and juicy on the inside. The oil used weren't stale.

The Beef Dried Hor Fun was also done nicely with wok hei, yet not too oily.

Restaurant ambience was chilled,

Ordered the Konoha Sannin, it came with their top 3 signature dishes, the Saba, tonkotsu and a5 wagyu slices. All three were really good.. think the Saba is orochimaru.. tonkotsu prolly jiraiya and wagyu gotta be Tsunade.. ü§£
Delicious nasi lemak with many items and also very cheap and worth itüëçüëçüëçüëç...just $1 only. One of the cheapest nasi lemak in Singapore üá∏üá¨ üëå üòÄ
Nice food

Best Thai food outside of Thailand. Ever. Soi Thai has outdone itself again. Food is authentic, staff incredible, and the owner so friendly. Today we ordered pad Thai, Tom Kha soup, seabass with Thai Chilli sauce, mango sticky rice, pineapple rice, and Thai iced teas for everyone. Menu feels like a dream team of Thai cuisine - any combi is guaranteed to impress. Kopkhunkrap Soi Thai Kitchen!

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Took a few dishes. Like the fried rice in the second picture and the vegetable puff in the first picture, better.
On 11 Dec 21, took New chicken salad, vegetable dumplings and pork collar sour vegetable in sour and spicy soup. Took glutinous rice cube in rice wine as dessert. Took hot milk tea Hong-Kong style.  As shown in the last 4 pictures. The vegetable dumplings and hot milk tea Hong-Kong style were commendable.

I ordered the xiao long bao, pan fried shrimp n meat dumplings, mala jajang noodles and the rosewater glutinous rice balls. Firstly the Xiao long bao, the skin on the top is on the thicker side and the meat filling was to mashy n the taste was off. The pan fried shrimp & meat dumplings was the star here! I can taste the well-marinated shrimp & meat, the skin was just the right thickness. The mala jajang noodles was so so.. noodles was a little too soggy for me and I would like it if more shredded cucumber was added to refresh the palate. I was surprised, they added fried tofu which was unusual but it was a great choice as they were really good; crispy outside and there were still bean curd left inside which was moist. The rosewater glutinous rice balls were also üëç Right doneness of the balls w peanut n sesame fillings and it wasn't too sweet (maybe for those who like sweets will find it bland but it was just right for me). I find the standard has dropped since I last visited! üòú

We had a small traditional claypot rice, a small claypot seafood fried beehoon, a small homemade crispy bean curd (10 pcs) and 4 Chinese tea to share among 4 pax. Total bill $38.60.

The food was yummy and everything was served hot and freshly cooked üëçüèª they gave us 4 bowls without having to ask for it and service was prompt.

Indoor seating was quite cooling and we actually felt like we were in malaysia due to the setting.

Only qualm was that we were all very thirsty abt half an hour after the meal which likely meant that there was quite a bit of msg in it. Otherwise, definitely worth a try and we will definitely go back and try their other dishes!

Jacks Place used to be a great Steak Restaurant in the 90's..till some time in 2000's.(Their outlet in Killiney Rd was very good).Then they stopped serving Pork products in their dishes..& Fillet Mignon Sizzler steak which had Crispy Bacon on it was revamped wth other items. Further..their service attention to customers had waned also..& Red Wine was served chilled..thus ruining its taste. Lastly like most Western food outlets in Singapore  they hardly have any hot vegetarian main dish offerings.. unlike in North America etc (where there are atleast 5-6 items to choose). Overall an average Restaurant wth 5 star prices.
Had great pork ribs and curry pork rice. Bulls eye fried egg on the rice had just the right balance of runny yolk and crisp edges on the whites.

Great quiet corner for Thai food! Introduced by a food friend to come here for affordable Thai cuisine. We got many dishes ( close to 6) and paid only about $25 - definitely overate.

You must try their Omelette wrap With seafood in tomato sauce. Fillings comprised seafood and mushroom chunks that are really tasty!

Dry sukiyaki glass noodles is also cooked pretty well, and you get a good mix of vegetables, chicken and prawns/springs.

Will definitely be back if I‚Äôm in the area!

Stall only operates on weekdays as this stall is in a canteen housed in the Creative Building
It has already attracted its pool of regulars despite just operating a few months...me included
Favourite dish for me is Soto Ayam...or Mee Soto if they run out out ketupat
Their chicken broth is full body flavoured...and one would easily slurp the bowl dry...
Their chicken slice servings are peeled off fresh chicken parts as seen from the white colored chicken slices..unlike most stalls which serve overbight chicken or parts that are barely edible
Top it up with their begedil...and the dish is complete...begedil is well prepared...moist and not soaking in used oil
Their nasi padang food choices are also well seasoned and prepared...certainly worth the calories on a diet cheat day
Good for eating there or takeaway if one does not like the crowd in the canteen
DELICIOUS
Overall not bad. The Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ tasted more at the sweet side though. Would definitely recommend the vinegar pork leg. Yummms!
I like the Zi Char they served here. Its above average. It's get crowded over the weekend. Call to reserve a table if u can.
Always doesn‚Äôt disappoint! In terms of service, and food! Definitely will come back again. Thanks!

Wonderful chill out and burst of flavourfl experience. They accommodate to your taste buds in cooking. Must tries are their murtabak, sardine satti soru. Drinks are reasonable and affordable. If you drink Guinness theirs is very refreshing.  If you drink whiskey their per bottle price is also reasonable. A fulfilled weekend hangout for me.

Tried a few items on their menu like their signature rice noodle, their braised chicken rice and their lu rou fan. They are really good. Really liked the pumpkin dessert as well it is really addictive. Opens early at 10am and service is really fast. Will definitely try again if possible.

Surprising find for us - was looking for bak kut Teh rather than zi char last for dinner. However we were not disappointed by this choice!

The steamed sharks head was of course, the highlight of the night. The taste of the 99.9% collagen based filing was excellent. The rest of the dishes, were good - and the overall cost was only S$85.

A cheap fix for your sushi craving. The sushi does tend to get left on the shelf for Long hours depending on the sales volume of the day.

It looks appetising and is a decent enough fix. However, the food has tasted/looked off several times towards the shop closing hours.

I would suggest adding different flavours of sushi to entice more customers to buy.

But I will return as their food is 3 stars worth of tastiness!
Good

Old school eatery that really delivers on price and quality. The setup is rather utilitarian, but the staff are attentive and welcoming.

The fish head curry is their famous dish which really delivers. The assam curry is tangy and spicy, touched by sweetness from the vegetables and pineapple. The fish head is meaty, unlike many places. All of it comes together to make a well-balanced whole.

On the downside, the famed Kyoto pork is a little dry and flavor doesn't seep all the way through the meat. Makes for a very instagrammable dish though because of it's flaming presentation.

Overall, the food is good and the price point is very reasonable, leaving you with a sense of satisfaction.

Ate here today... Bought 2 normal and 2 butter prata. Couldn't believe it was $9. That's still fine, but the cashier was super rude, and I saw the staff dip his whole finger into the curry!

Super nasty, not coming back again.

A regular places I would go for my daily dinner or lunches..

They have great cook and their dishes are very savory even when the places are fully crowded, their standard of the food never fails!

Staffs are very attentive and polite. I would recommend for great cze char and various dishes are always my favourite.

Service Quality: 7/10
Food Quality: 8/10
Pricing: Reasonable
Ambience: 6/10 (though its a coffeeshop, but it's very neat and clean)

Complete rip off. My first and most definitely my last time eating there ever.
Had a few of their individual dishes and all of it tasted terrible. Oh and the prawn sambal, No idea why it was so sweet. I almost thought I was eating some sort of dessert.

All good but not exceptional, good for a no-frills meal. Service is ok, food is not too bad, price is affordable but not cheap. Tried the 2 pax curry fish head set which came with tahu goreng and 2 rice for $19.90. The dishes took awhile to prep but came hot. The fish was only half, slightly small. Tahu goreng was done right and portion was good. The curry was good! However, it can be too spicy and sour for many. Order extra kang kong which was cold, but taste-wise is good. Overall i would say taste and variety is good but price, portion and service have some room for improvement.

POSITIVES:

Food was alright, all the dishes were yummy and pretty good. Soft shell crab maki was yummy had this yuzu dressing inside which was refreshing. Staff were lovely trying to compensate for robot‚Äôs technical failures. Poor design feature. No call button to get staff‚Äôs attention, need to stand up to walk to the staff..
Being led to our table by TEMI robot was a novel experience.

NEGATIVES:
Spicy salmon sushi came smelling weird and like smelly socks + tasted weird too.

Ordered salmon belly sashimi. Never came. One robot came but inside was empty. The order  was marked as completed order. After a few requests, staff came personally to serve it.

Pieces of ham stuck to the bottom of my vegetarian eggplant sandwich. :(

Edit: I msged on FB and they kindly offered me a refund or another sandwich free of charge!! :)
food delicious n nice service

food here is great but the timing displayed here is a scam. google stated that the store will be opened till 10.30pm on a saturday but arrived and they said they‚Äôre closed for the day at 9.30pm (we arrived at 9.15pm) -,-

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: I won't say there is any ambience...this is a traditional large spaced restaurant. However, they make it up with pretty quality for the food they serve-food not that cheap. A bit hard to find for first timers, so WAZE up. Parking not cheap-I paid $8 for my lunch hours. I would bring the older folks for that touch of the old days
Value for money..(Filipino) food is good, nice place to chill.. drinks r limited
First time here. Nice place and crowded on a weekend lunch period. Ordered the Burrito chicken wrap and bowl chicken. Recommended to have with spice. Nice overall!

Nice and fresh,I tried the don here, is delicious.can have a try when pass by poiz centreüëç

Like

Answer

Tried the char koay teow and it‚Äôs really below expectations for a Penang style dish. Not sure why there‚Äôs so many patrons here during lunch time. Perhaps the taste buds for real authentic standard of Penang food has mutated to Singapore local taste style of Penang Char Koay Teow?

Never knew Mutton can be so tender. Had the mutton hot plate and the naan was the best I‚Äôve had-garlicky, fresh and warm! Chicken tandoori too sweet for my liking. $17.50 including lime juice for 2 pax. Very filling but a bit salty for me
Love their zichar dishes, especially the ÁÉ§È±ºÁâáÁâáÈ¶ô & ÈáëÊ±§ËÇ•Áâõ. Great food at reasonable price. Portions are of good size. Will definitely return again!

Went over for a weekday lunch. Not crowded. Price is reasonable for an aircon place although it's in an industrial area. I found the chee cheong fun over-rated and mine was served cold. It has a nice fragrance from the taste of shallots and that's it. We saw they were busy so didn't feedback. Not sure if it is better on other times as feedback from others here were good.
We enjoyed the curry chicken and assam noodles although it's a little watery. Nice coffee and tea. Will return to try the yam cake, porridge and nasi lemak.
Food is good and the environment quite nice to enjoy your indian cuisine.
Very posh food is good portions just nice..Good food excellent for business talk.

For some heartlander Japanese /Korean food, I think this is one of the better stalls around. They have a few outlets across the island also. Of course they are not your authentic Japanese or Korean cuisine that you would die for, but the taste is somewhat there. With such affordae prices and their portion of a meal is value for money, I can't complain.

Most of their food are made to order. Mostly are fried or teppanyaki style. The usual sauces or ingredients are teriyaki, Japanese mayonnaise, katsu items, pickled vegetables and Kimchi.

Their hotplate soba fish looks quite popular here. It comes with a seaweed soup and rice. Their bento sets looks nice too. In total they have about 40 items on the menu.

Overall its good enough to eat for lunch and dinner if you just bored of Chinese or western food.
Nice Indian restaurant

Chanced upon this while we were trying to visit a fried rice stall at the same coffeeshop during its rest day on Mon.

Really competent bowl of ramen at coffeeshop prices - chasu is flavourful and sliced to a good thickness, ajitama has perfect molten yolk and absorbed the soy sauce, tonkotsu broth and ramen are well executed. The spicy black oil was different from what I tried at some Japanese ramen restaurants, tasted a little bit like light curry broth.

Interesting to have more international influences coming into the coffeeshop scene.

Bought the Loh Mai Gai, Lotus Bun and Red Bean Bun. Price was reasonable. The quality was good, ingredients were fresh and taste was yummy. Will buy again.
Updated on 7 Sep 2022:
Had the Char Kway Teow and Char Siew Wanton noodles. CKT was good, delicious and flavourful, with 2 prawns, plenty of bean sprouts and pork lard. The noodles on the other hand was average, the Char Siew was too fatty. Soup was nice.

Started patronising due to good deals available on shopee. Tried the char kway teow and love it. Popiah is huge, very worthwhile if using shopee voucher bought at promo price, else taste wise is just ok, nothing to rave about. Haven't tried other food but the curry noodle definitely smell good, will try next. Staff are not with the best attitude but also not as bad as how some have described. At least I didn't encounter. About 5 visits made.
Not many stalls are opened. Price are consider high as this is only canteen to foodcourt environment. Not really worth.
Awesome Prata with or without egg. And a punch with mutton curry. They are good! The curry is rich and tasty. The mutton has no smell of goat.

You should really look into ur food portion. Food delivered was only less than half of the box.
And pricing was not comparable to the portion. I hope u can improve on that.
Also we ordered to break fast and obviously not enough for even 1 person share.
Rather for a kids portion.
Truly disappointing.

Good quality Thai food at reasonable (and affordable) prices. Helped to settle my family‚Äôs craving for Thai food, without needing to travel to Golden Mile. The parking is very limited for dinner crowd though, as the nearest parking spaces are mostly reserved for season parking after 7pm.

Decent food but cannot deny a dip in standards over the last 2 years. Not easy to find tissue prata around but was slightly disappointed with a plain, tasteless tissue prata, had to add sugar ourselves üòÖ Can skip the teh tarik too unfortunately
Would be great if McDonald's app deals are redeemable here

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Very well maintained market and food center upstairs. Regular evening cleaning by the town council. Great food in the food center upstairs such as the Joon Heng Noodle stall selling chicken feet noodle, 88 congee, duck rice, Hup Lee Fried Mee Hoon selling economy bee hoon and come daily hokkien mee which is my favorite. There is a snack stall on the ground level and this uncle sells really fresh snacks, his opening hours is in regular and do have plenty of patience to purchase your snack...
The grilled fish is nice.  With the price of $19.80, can get a fish with 4 vege as sides. Cheaper a lot than other grilled fish shop at city area. Worth a try.
Ordered the set for 2, just nice. Soup come w 6 fresh prawns which 3 of them are big, worth the $. Reasonable price n worth to try. Highly recommend.
Usual hang out place for nice food n decent price

Gu Ma Jia kitchen is simple and unpretentious. What you see is what you get

Sometime simplicity is all you need. Don‚Äôt need the pompous and filtered photos which looks good but end results is disappointing.

It was a celebration for a colleague returning for a short stint at Korea.

There were 5 of us hence five dishes.

Service and waiting time were generally ok. As this was a treat by the boss, I didn‚Äôt know the actual price. However I have glance at the menu and the prices are reasonable.

Certain dish only come in standard size whilst other have different sizes. Make sure you check when ordering. You can ask them to help you estimate the dish size based on your group size.

My favourite dish was the Asam fish filet. They packed a punch in terms of sour and spiciness. On that day they ran out of the whole fish hence the filet.

If you crave for home taste cooked food, I would recommend this kitchen.

Famous local steamed chicken with ginger and lettuce to wrap it or with steamed rice. Nice try and the steamed minced pork with salted fish also taste delicious.Very good selections of food, also with a good service. I was accompanied by a local colleague speaking Chinese so I have no idea if English would be a problem. Anyway, nothing to complain, I recommend it.

My 1st visit to the famed Rasa Sayang Western and I ordered the steak with mushroom sauce. I asked for medium and it came out perfectly done and taste factor was definitely very good for coffeeshop standards! Will definitely be back to try other dishes!

Ambience is good.
A bit on the expensive side.
Food is well presented but nothing fantastic.
Service - nothing much to talk about.

The food and ambience was pretty good. I really liked the sukiyaki glass noodles. The green curry was slightly underwhelming as there was too much coconut milk in my opinion. But on a whole price was worth the meal!
I really like the fried bun as it tastes really good! I like it! Also, the ÁîúÂøÉÂÖ´ÂÆùÈ•≠ surprises me too as I have never tried this kind of food before. Will definitely be back to eat again!

The food was delicious especially from the cfud stall , seating arrangement sufficient , clean and well ventilated dining space
Only the drinks prices were overpriced compared to other eating outlets

Lots of choices to choose from. Tried the fried fish soup and it was very tasty. Fish is served separately in a bowl so it does not come soggy and soft. Also tried the fish meat white bee hoon. Freshly cooked and hot, very good. Will come again.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: Affordable, fresh and tasty sushi. They provide sauce, wasabi and chopsticks. I wish they have outlet near my workplace.

Seems typical Thai food .. everything was on the sweet side of usual Thai cuisine .. the vermicelli is pretty decent .. satay pork is nicely done .. tender and nicely seasoned .. ate on a very windy and idyllic day .. overall feel is not bad

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Don't even deserve a star, can't even be bother even to take a photo. Standard , service as well as quality is pretty bad for an big restaurant. Soup base tasted like boiling water vegetables is as big as those that are selling in the market. Would love to comment more on facts however it doesn't worth my time to do that so friends all I can say Is visit at your own risk.

Food is mediocre and average. Place is well-decorated and looks good from the outside. Assam fish we ordered was not fresh. Sambal potato leaves is near tasteless. Prawn Paste Chicken wasn't too bad. Gst and sevice charge is inclusive in the dish price. Hits and misses in their food. May come back here again if they improve.
Always says kitchen is closed. Only can order non-vege rice set. Others than that cannot order.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Delicious Nasi Lemak! Sambal isn‚Äôt the spiciest but they portioned a generous amount of it. Chicken is crispy and other ingredients were nice too!

The last time l went to Springleaf Prata was 7 to 8 years ago. The place has been spruced up. It's brighter, airier, cleaner and feel more spacious. The best part is it no longer smell heavily of curry and oil which stick to your clothes and hair.

Unfortunately, the standard of the food has gone southwards. We ordered a number of stuffs, from prata to murtabak to maggi goreng to nasi biryani. Only the prata withstood the taste test. The rest left much to be desired. The maggi goreng lacks 'wok hei' and the chicken meat in wre all dry and rubbery.  The meat in the murtabak is quite bland, so overall the dish lacks oomph and flavour. The mutton nasi biryani was very average. I've tasted better ones even in neighbourhood coffee shops.

While the self service curry gravy seems like a good idea, the gravy offered here are a bit too watery and not flavorful enough.

This is just at the entrance when you exit from Farrer Park MRT into the mall. Was quite surprised that there is a food court here. Definitely a strong competitor to Food Republic at the top floor. I think this is similar to Yishun North Point. The Bak Kut Teh tastes similar. Only 2 pork ribs & a few slices of meat. The saving grace is the sambal belacan. It really got kick. Chendol ($2) is less generous than the one I had in North Point.
Sitting capacity is small. Might have trouble finding seats.
Good and cheap halal nasi padang at kim keat. Carpark at blk 76 in lorong limau.

Highly under staff. Service is very slow. Our cooked food took a while to reach and the beer comes later than cooked stuff, something that no need to cook comes later than the cooked ones is super weird. We need to call for the server a few times before we were "noticed".

Good decent variety of thai dishes. Steamed fish is excellent if you enjoy fish! Thai fish cake and Kao Pao Gai is good too. Red ruby desert is bad. The shaved ice is coarse, the syrup taste just sweet. Overall food good; desert bad.
blk 73 curry fish head good mac 4pax fot 12$ cheap and good. other 8 to 12$. try try...

very nice congee and i went for set meal. will go again. staffs are very friendly and efficient.
very crowded place and seating area quite small.
Only came here for prata and teh halia‚Ä¶shiok. Service does get very slow when they are busy so come during off peak. Egg prata price is now $2.00 üôÄ halal neighborhood restaurant

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Good place for hawker food.... Run by generation of local. Must try this old fashioned wanton noodle. 2nd dish to try is the fish soup. Freshness is ok. Special feature is the seaweed piece in it.

Dine in always the best choice if u wanna eat claypot. But due to the limited seat we choose to tapao.

They provide online delivery but have to meet a min $30 (will charge delivery fees)
Free delivery within 3km from the store.

Recommend their claypot & sanlou beehoon. This two eat with their chilly will be perfect.

Ordered Indian rojak and Nasi goreng ikan bilis.

Rojak tasted almost similar to the original one at Ayer rajah food centre.

The Nasi goreng lacks the ‚Äúkick‚Äù but still good.

I must say, the service can be improved. Most of the times, they‚Äôre talking to one another.

Knew it was pricey when i went. Still got taken aback when bill came. Haha

Food is good. Roast duck good. Charred char siew is power. Roasted meat is good too.  Noodles are very Q.

Dumpling soup is mediocre.

Don‚Äôt know about the service as there was no dine in due to covid. But tar pow was fast and pleasant. Will definitely go back as i did not expect michelin service with the michelin pricing.

$3.50 for a choice of A, B or C basis set. Not the cheapest, but addition of sambal goreng for $1, and the same for a piece of Otak was much more reasonable.

Coconut milk rice with a drop of pandan leaf juice giving it a slight green hue and stronger fragrance. Chicken wing was overcooked and dry. Sambal sweet. Everything else was real normal.

Average. So I don't understand the constant line seen here. Thankfully fast moving.
Lobster porridge very nice. Black pepper beef is tender. Marmite ribs tasty. Yam paste is average.
Love the porridge. It tasted very good but took sometimes to get the order. No queue but waiting time about 20 minutes plus to get the order on lunch time.
Fried dishes such add Kuay Teow and Sambal Kang Kong full of Wok Hei and robust aroma.  Reasonable priced with generous serving.

Service of Yalong Bay is good and staff are approachable and friendly as well. Reservation is also allowed. However, the food is not as tasty. The lala Hor fun supposed to be popular tasted starchy. The prawn paste chicken wings and deer meat with onion were also not tasty as those we took in other coffee shops. The burning chicken, we didn‚Äôt get to try as needs to call for reservation one day in advance. Other shops, the western food took 40 mins to serve our orders but didn‚Äôt taste good either. Either over fried or oily. Kids couldn‚Äôt finish it at all. On TOP of that, the place is very hot although the aircon is on. Only attention is the beer pricing.. 5 of bottles for $30 - $35

The service staff were very polite and professional even though it was packed with customers and all the tables were full

The food was served hot and it was delicious with many varieties of Putien and Hokkien cuisines to choose from.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Was there with my 44th years primary school classmate. Love the ambience and the food was fabulous yet very affordable . Definitely highly recommended

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Great service. The grilled meats were delicious. At a good price point. Service staff were wonderful and friendly!
Taste is average. Service is okay. If not for the lunch menu, then not worth it.
The standard dropped. Murtabak portion is like egg prata size. Don't order

It was a Public Holiday, and we headed out to Toa Payoh for something different. Chanced upon Tim's Restaurant not too far from our favourite chicken rice, and what a gem it turned out to be. This simple Nepalese joint serves up very decent western fare. Besides they have excellent staff with immense patience with the customers! Is recommended this once to anyone, but don't take MY word for it; go try for yourself!
More like traditional restaurants,  my daughter wedding dinner, going again next week for father's day dinner

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Hot and spicy fish  and stir fry yellow beef. Wonderful, spicy but not the extreme.

Today we had a impromptu lunch at Toriyard. Supposed to be 8 of us however some didn't manage to join us. The chef is very courteous during introduction of the menu. We especially like the lady server who sent us our food!! Heard that it was her 1st day there..Keep up the good work!!üëçüèªWill definitely be backüòä
Fried chicken wings freshly cooked. You can see the golden brown of the crispy crust!

Been here a couple of times, most returning almost weekly. The claypot chicken is one of their signature and defo worth trying, hotplate beancurd with egg and chinglong vege with beansprouts are yummy great too. Also try the bbq pork bun! I like that portion sizes are reasonable and food comes relatively fast. It also has a nice homemade feel to it.
Lovely place for traditional family gathering. Service was great, food was even better. My mom and my uncle love all the dishes we've ordered!
Best halal japanese food at a very heartland price. Fulfilling and very delicious. Will certainly repeat if i at kim keat market area. Try. No regrets

Disappointing experience. The fish+spicy fish roe from the seasonal menu which I ordered came with raw parts in the fish. I only realised the raw parts halfway through my meal. After I checked with the waitress, she took the plate and said she'd "return it to the kitchen", without waiting for a response.

After 10minutes, the plate was just thrown on my table, with the waitress mumbling "‰∏çÂ•ΩÊÑèÊÄùÂïä" ("sorry ah") and walked away, again without waiting for any response. And guess what, the fish came back still in its half eaten form (photo attached), albeit cooked more thoroughly. In this COVID-19 climate, not sure if putting back a half-eaten fish on the grill is a good idea.

There was obviously no room for discussion on the possible service recovery. No sincere apologies given, no offering of any compensation. Even though it is a grave issue regarding food safety.
Had the Chope deal which was the Premium Buta Don. The pork was so tender and juicy. The sauce was a little sweet and savoury. And that char on the meat was divine. Love it!

they got variety of food & most of'em are  tasty.
takeaway service  was not good .There can be plenty of miscommunication can be happened during takeaway

The cashier indian lady has attitude problem at prata raya ang mo kio hub outlet. She is not friendly at all and never smiles when taking your order like not happy doing her job. I ordered egg briyani and charged me sgd 5.80 and my order came out the briyani rice with just 1 fried egg. Usually Last time they gave me 2 round fried boiled egg. I did ask her if there is egg bryani but she never even bothered to inform me that there is no stock and only have fried egg. Feel cheated with this overprice egg briyani. The management of this prata house need to consider this staff. Thanks

Worst e dining experience. Ordered a main course. Waited 40 mins, the waiter come tell me it was not prepare. Multiple wrong food and beverage was serve.

Every food need to ask, then only will serve!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Extremely rude waitress who thoght no end of herself! Placed order via foodpanda with pick up scheduled at 1246, 1 skinny sharp voice waitress in her 50s shouted at me that they didn't follow foodpanda timing, they had the choice to delay my order by 30mins! Don't understand why the restaurant paid such a staff to chase customers away!

Malaysian HupKee Fishball @ Blk 158 Ang Mo Kio Avenue 4 Coffee Shop. You will see breakfast crowd everyday except Monday. The handmade fishball are very ‚ÄúQ‚Äù. If you have 20-30mins time allowance to queue up can try it up. Good thing must wait !!!

Visited this restaurant a couple times. The restaurant is located alongside several eateries on Jalan Kayu. On both visits, the restaurant was not very crowded and we got a table immediately.
Service is good from arriving at restaurant, ordering food and waiting time.
On this visit, I ordered the curry fishhead. The taste is perfectly balanced and really delicious.
The shop is also kept very clean and bright.
Overall experience is very good.
Good Chinese restaurant quality food at reasonable prices. Nice ambience - quieter, less hectic. Suggest for you to make reservation first before heading down especially for bigger groups.

Located at level 2, and you can only access it via 1 escalator, nowhere else.
Not very accessible, though there is a nearby bus stop.
Well decorated place with many food stalls. It's a food court with aircon selling food from many cuisines and the place is huge!
Tze char, western, korean cuisine, army stew/mookata, drinks.
At the back of the place, the drinks stall sells snacks and many beers! They seem affordable!
Came here for Gogiyo, but might come again for other stalls

15/04/22
Mee rebus over rated. There are better ones. The satay is ok but still lack of flavour. However, the meat portion is generous unlike other satay sellers.

Food is ok. The black sauce noodles was nothing but salty.. salted egg pork ribs was covered in batter w almost no meat at all. Claypot rice is the only decent thing here, guess that‚Äôs why that‚Äôs their store name. Give this a miss because in this area there is bound to have better food!

(Translated by Google) The attitude of the staff is very bad. When ordering things, their store has no loose money, so they told me that there is loose money? Don't eat without money! Bad attitude, don't work, you can go home, don't come out and go crazy

Chicken garlic pasta is good. The large calamari rings are crispy and nice as well.
I loved the food, service and staff! Great selection of food. Wonderful atmosphere and ambience. 10/10 would come again. Ps wear a jacket, it‚Äôs cold!
Basic Japanese noodle.

We attended the dumpling cooking class and learned how to make dumblings with 3 different fillings from scratch (we even did the dough ourselves). It is a lovely place, the session was well organized and the cooking stations are spacious and well equipped. We will definitely try it again at home üòä - highly recommended!
Best breakfast n lunch
Food is good, would be perfect if they are more generous with the onion rings

Affordable and delicious sirloin steak at a coffee shop in Toa Payoh.
Will try their fried chicken the next time.

The food is really good. Good ambience for a restaurant to be situated in an educational institution. I love the flavour of the food and one of the better orh nee yam paste dessert. Will go again. So good that we left nothing behind. The crab is not their best dish though. I will omit the crab. The sauce is good, the problem is the size of the crab. Not big enough. Opt for bigger size crab should solve the problem.

food was good. a little bit pricey.
We pop out for lunch, there were only 2 costumers at that time. and its not busy.
we called out to the filipina (black hair around 40-ish) waitress, and she seemed not very happy abt her work. lol. very impolite and impatient. i asked her to take us a photo before we devour our food lol, but she just waived her hand and walked out. i would‚Äôve understand if the store was busy, but it isn‚Äôt. lol
very poor costumer service. smh.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Went on a Saturday night. Sorry but... Worst zichar I've ever tasted :/ Small portions, slow service... Could the crowd be only because the rest of the shops have a really long queue? On top of being not so great the prices were high. It ‚Ä¶

Ordered the pineapple fried rice, basil pork rice, tomyum soup. All dishes were flavourful and good! Staff is also very friendly when taking our orders, and also helped to bring the food to our table. A hidden gem in the area.
The mermaid dish nice. Service crew can be abit over friendly by keep coming to your table to ask if you want to order when you are still waiting for friend to arrive.
interior design looks dope, foods great too!
Yummy food! Recommend the charcoal waffles and their triple chocolate ice cream!

Place : seats not enough
Food : good
Penang laksa has no sardine ‚Ä¶

Affordable, delicious and very authentic tasting thai food. Restaurant was clean and well air-conditioned. Great place to grab a bite and chill. Loved their recommended drunken noodle which was spicy. Fortunately, me and my wife love spicy food. Their pineapple fried rice was bursting with flavour too. I'll definitely come back for more.
Absolutely lovely experience. Food was great and the hosts kept our party happy and lively. Omg! Go soi47!

Shang jian bun skin is too thick. Pork chop fried rice is deep fried with powder coated different frm usual and rice is tasteless. Barley is cheap and nice. Guo tie and XLB so so only.Wine chicken too salty. Price is reasonable and service is good.
Nice place. Not too crowded. Serves fast.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Majority of the food are good but price is getting high. I believe should be across all hawker centres. The fried hokkien prawn noodle is good üëç
Had the Masala Crabs, Fish Head Curry with Naans. Tasted really good.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Recommended by son, as I have not heard of this chicken rice before. (I am not a chicken rice fan)
And was surprised with the high rating. So we went with high expectations.
Rice was fragrance and came quite a small portion.
The roasted chicken meat was soft and tender. The sauce was too sweet for my liking.
At least there are some dishes that we can order beside eating chicken meat.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Horrible Midnight experience whereby the Indian staffs are just bad at communication with customers and plainly just interested in sitting down with their mobiles than working. Management also didn‚Äôt give two hoots about running the place properly and just sitting around.

Ordered twice on the menu with several items and no updates on item that are unavailable. Had to take 3 staff to update me on closing timing

Staff constantly crowding over table when it‚Äôs near closing to pressure us to finish up quickly when no proper handover on what time they‚Äôre really closing. Everything was estimated.

Billing was horrible where items are just listed on how many quantities of the price tag we took which we can‚Äôt tally if the item is there on the table or just added randomly. Bill is not shocking but could use more work to let customers understand what is charged

Been to different outlets and also this outlet in other timing but never had this horrible experience even when it‚Äôs super shorthanded. Makes me think twice on whether I‚Äôm gonna patronise there as a fellow F&B server

Warm and friendly service. The online reservation (via Chope platform) is not working so reserved table by calling them. As usual, the food was amazing. Yummy, yummy, yummy. Expect about $25 to $40 per person price range.

Great sauce that adds bountiful flavor to the loklok. 1 dollar per stick. Variety is okay but can be better. Quite fast service and cooking. Good value and generally this coffee shop is hipster with good variety of other food to go with. Recommended.

The newly revamped Japanese food hall has many new and enjoyable choices, from Ramen to Gohan. The Saba Shioyaki Set ($11.90) and Beef Rice Set ($14.90) from My Gohan were both good and the furnishings were refreshing.
Big place for dining. Friendly service staff but food are ordinary like any neighbourhood hor fan stall. Tea and coffee are good though.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: A no non-sense Chinese style ‚Äústreet‚Äù food with a little restaurant flare.  The ‚ÄúSan Lao‚Äù Hor Fun is a must try (stir-fried flat rice noodles with fish & bean sprouts gravy sauce).  Expect a little waiting time if there are a lot of people.  Pass your time waiting for food by watching the service ladies talking (or shouting?) to each other in Chinese.  Recommended for cheap, local eats.

Ordered the Sheng Jian Bao and soya bean drink for lunch. Loved the slightly doughy buns that were bursting with delicious meat juices. It was a lovely and refreshing lunch, especially when paired with the ice cold soya bean drink on a hot day.

Went back again for dinner with family. This time, ordered the Sheng Jian bao, Xiao long Bao, noodle soup with preserved vegetables and pork and noodles with pork in spicy sauce.
Family likes the buns- both the fried and steamed ones. However, the noodles were a disappointment.

Service was excellent and attentive. However the tables were placed too near to each other. Was not comfortable dining next to another customer who was sniffling away the entire meal and he was seated less than a metre away.
Quick fix delicious meal option! Price for most of the sides have been on a constant rise, passively...

This is lousy food!!! Feel angry to eat!! This is last we eat at amk restaurant collin!!! Pork rib charcoal the meat is cold!!! What the chef experience of this?? Just learning to cook? This is last we eat at collin....

Service is efficient, dishes served quickly especially at peak lunch hour. Heng Hwa bee hoon tasty, though a little too oily, and has sufficient ingredients and condiments added. Stir fried razor class gong bao style was enjoyable as they were willing to tone down the spice. Bian rou soup was alright though not very impressive.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content:
Non-bitter chicken essence, tastes like chicken soup.
My kids love it. Definitely worth it!

The food was nice but little bit salty for the noodles and their staffs are friendly. They are busy as business is good. Need to improve on their alertness, like refilling of tea. Raises my hands a few time, also cannot catches their attention, almost want to give them a call to fill my tea.
Chicken Chop + 1 x sausage for $7.50. Portion is small and don't taste that good. Not worth my moneu

I was there early to order food around 10:10. However the outlet would only serve customer from 10:30 onward. The waiter is rude to tell me off. With the advancement of service standard in singapore, it is rare to have similar experience.

Affordable Thai food in Braddell area. Ordered the lunch set basil pork rice with green curry. The green curry is rather creamy, basil pork rice comes with a fried egg and is decent without being too spicy. Overall good value for money if you are around the area.

Bought chicken chop to try. The sides were salad and mashed potato. Chicken chop was nice, grilled to perfection but the sauce provided was too little. Fries were not bad, a little bland though. Salad was refreshing and crunchy. Mashed potato tasted like flour, bland and powdery. Service was alright.

We are being reminded a few time it's last order at about 8.20pm to 8.30pm. At 8.40pm where most of my family have already finish their dinner and I am really hungry. I was being told they forgotten to cook my dinner. I waited for 50 minutes and they actually forgotten to cook for me. Sadly, there is no crowd at all and this mean they're NOT busy at all. The service crew and the kitchen aren't busy at all. It's not my style to rate a one star unless this really bad service experience.
Love their pineapple rice. Decent pricing. Good selection of food on their menu. Food is very homely. Recommended.
Thai restaurant with  foods cooked & place run by Mainland Chinese.  Service mediocre & we're  not going back again.

Discovered this place 4yrs ago and the standards have maintained. Excellent gado-gado (peanut sauce over rice cake, cabbage, tau kwa, tempeh, potato, keropok). Tasty and rich peanut sauce. Food items also fresh and just all round well-made. The mee soto is also good and they have good quality potato cutlet.

#localguides #gadogado
A pretty good meal with great tasting dishes.  The prices are very reasonable.  I would go there again for sure üëçüëçüëç
Nice halal Korean food cook by professional chef

Came on weekday evening.
No queue. But most table are under reserve.

Service ok. Pro-active but not flexible.

Food Nice. However their bake potato no longer the same I use to taste before. üôÉ

Garlic bread soggy ‚Äî ü´§

Will recommend to make reservation prior to it.

It's a nice place to have lunch or dinner, only because it is air conditioned, parking is super convenient, and not many people truly know of this place yet. It's very cool how they have so many different types of craft beers on display, and how the prices are much more reasonable compared to the bars and pubs we know. The food here is also very well curated, whether it is the tse char stall, the western food, or the malay Muslim food stall. Quite impressed.

Front counter staff is a vietnamese girl and she does not even understand english and mandarin at all so it takes her a long time to get me the right order. It is a waste of time for me. Pls employ someone who understand basic english or mandarin if he or she will to be in frontline.
Very bad service. Food quality has also gone down!

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content:
Extremely long waiting time. Ordered at about 7:20PM but even at 7:52PM the food is still not here yet.

EDIT: It's ok already the food was great thank you

Sad to said it‚Äôs just a normal steakhouse in a coffee shop.

45mins of waiting time is way too long for a small portion of steak on a hot plate which cost $16 dollars.

The side dish only offer less then 1/4 of tomato, 1 fried mash potato and small portion of baked bean. If they change it to the bake potatoes with toppings + some carrots and broccoli. That will be better.

The only good point is that the beef is soft and tender.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
It was my first time to try mookata.
It satisfied me and ingredients were fresh.
Tastes so good
Recommended
SUPER YUMMY, TRY THE LAVA CAKE
Marvelous north Indian food. Highly recommended!
their pulled pork burger is awesome!!!

Feels like a food court eatery. There was a musky smell indoors, and there was only one wait staff (who seemed tired even though the shop just opened) on a Sunday lunch. Expected good food due to the many good reviews, but alas somehow my family didn't like the food we ordered. Even the basic udon broth has not much flavour and is just a salty broth. Sorry we won't be back.

I liked Malaysia food very much. Been supporting these outlets since it opened. However. I realized the standard of food dropped. The taste deteriorate. Eventhough after I suggested to the black shirt manager. The food did not improve. It came to the point that I finally made up my mind. Not to patronise the food stall anymore. Reasons being :
1) pricey. And portion is disappointing. Eat but cannot fill the stomach even with the large portion bought.
2) food is served with few or little tiny portions of meat and prawns or just 2 prawns. Few bean sprouts and few scattered eggs only for char kway teow or prawn noodle.
3) charged for every single box when asked to separate mee from soup for takeaway. When you did not make plastic bag availabkw for packing the noodles.
4) less than desirable attitude of the staff. That when you stand in queue in front of the cash register. They tend to ignore you and do their own cooking and delivery orders instead of politely asking you to hold on a while. This happened when I was at singpost at 1030an. Non peak hours.

In view of the above. My decision is not to patronise these stall any time in the near future. As for the price and portion. I have better options to fill my stomach somewhere else.

Thank you for scrimping on the portions thereby maximising your profits during this period.
Good luck for your business.

Came on Thursday 5.30pm, had a line and waited for about 10mins to place our order.

We had the fish & chips, chicken wings w Cajun rice and mushroom soup.

My thoughts:
Fish & chips was the battered kind!!!!! Something to be mentioned as it is not common to find battered fish outside of restaurant establishment. The fish was rather thick and well seasoned, the batter was really light and crispy. The tatar sauce that came w it seems like self-made and was strong on the raw onion taste. It matches well with the fish. $7.50 for this battered fish and chips is a steal.

Chicken wings w cajun rice on the other hand was alright. The chicken wings was slightly soggy, but well seasoned. The cajun rice had a pretty strong smoky taste, probably from capsicums. It came w 1 slice of broccoli. Overall feel of this dish was meh.

Mushroom soup is really good, different from outside. The ingredients was blended really finely, so not much mushroom chunks (abit sad tho). However the taste of the soup is very yummy and didn't feel too jelat. I could probably down 2 bowls of it.

Going to come back to try out their grills as we heard so many people ordering their steaks while eating.

Highly overrated. If this was a restaurant in Hong Kong I doubt they would have any visitors.

Not bad bad, just very average. Best dish we had was the baby Kai Lan, which was well-prepared and tasty. The rest was a bland mix of averageness.

I‚Äôm still sitting at the table and I‚Äôm already super thirsty. ‚ÄúMay the MSG be with you‚Äù, as they say in Star Wars.
