Very affordable yakiniku! Service is good and they have a mobile queuing system so you don't have to wait in line.

Downside is there's some cold spots on the electric grill.

I did not know that the sausage egg prata had cheese in it and I am lactose intolerant. I went to the manager and told him my dilemma, he was very nice to make fresh ones for me without cheese. Really grateful for the manager to go out of his way to replace it for me free.

Highly recommend to dine here for prata or supper. :)
Sirloin steak sucks, chicken cutlet, and fish and chips ok. Mediocre!

New Chirashi Restaurant, tried it on three different occasions and the standard & quality of the food is quite consistent.

They are very generous with the seafood and the rice has an additional flavour to it.

Tried the mentai salmom cheese don, kinda look like yu sheng (lol), was slightly too complex and heavy for my tastebuds, but my friend really enjoyed it.

The Bara Hana Salmon bowl was good, with pretty edible flowers. Love the freshness of the fish with a slight hint of sweetness from the egg & the pink floss thingie.

Friend had Sakana and we all really enjoy the tuna in the bowl & the huge cuts of sashimi.

Can try their chanwanmushi too, very different & refreshing.

A decent ramen sold in a coffeeshop stall.

Soup: Decent
Noodles: Decent
Price: Decent

Nothing special. Precisely because it is not something special but a comfort food that you could (or used to) have frequently that make it special. Not something outlandish, but a well balanced taste that would evoke the feel of passing the North South Malaysia highway where you pit stop for lunch üòâ.
Excellent Thai food, great service and great prices too. Will definitely be back!

Made a reservation for a small family event. Private room provided was spacious for the number of tables booked. Came with karaoke. Very nice and cosy space for get-together and catching up. Service was good in general. Food was superb and did not disappoint. Very tasty and adequately portioned. Pricing was also very fair. Definitely left the restaurant with good memories and great vibes. Parking is open air, plenty and cheap.

Assistant manager by the name of Mark was extremely rude and had a terrible attitude.
When asked how long the waiting time would be, he responded with an awful tone. Even rolled his eyes at us as he was walking away.
Authentic n Economical Thai Food. Passionate n Friendly Hawker
Fresh, tasty, authentic, down-to-earth thai food. Highly recommended! Especially the tom yum and steamed seabass :)
Second time visit this restaurant. Love the noodles and warm hearty soup. The ingredients are fresh and the portion is big. Worth the price. Would definitely come back again.
Great value and price for 2kg of meat. Super nice and chill industrial ambience with great service and chilli. Even have reward card. Worth every penny! Will come again soon!

Ordered takeaway. I like how they give a buzzer even for takeaways.

I got their chicken wing rice. The chicken wings were good. Well marinated without being overly salty. It comes with a sunny side up egg and coleslaw as well. I have to say their rice portion is quite big. But the disappointing thing is that the rice served is just plain rice. I was kind of expecting it to be have some flavour because there are some stalls which offer chicken wings with flavoured rice like those you get from chicken rice stalls. But overall worth the value.

U do not deserve any good review

Irresponsible zi char stall üòëüòëüòë

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
food was not bad a little bit pricey? but i think its the normal price?
has quite a wide variety and includes a drink bar and their in store washrooms
its a pretty good place to feel the restaurant vibe

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Busy but awesome spot for chicken rice with other side dishes as well. Lines up are usually pretty quick because they server fast and prices are decent for a full sit down. I usually come back here when the stalls don't cut it - enjoy

Never ever order via food apps. They use their own drivers but delivered my food at 21:30 when i ordered it at 18:30. They never answered the phone despite calling multiple tines. It is clearly an horrible customer experience and the food arrived iced called.

Great ambience. Staffs are very polite and attentive. Some waiting time due to reduce seatings. Food servings are quite fast and all very nicely presented. Currently they are running a GSS 50% off Wagyu steak @ 37.50+  comes with a drink, side veg bowl, soup and garlic bread. Very worth it. Steak is nicely done n juicy. Soup is tasty and good to go with the crispy garlic bread.
A place where lights are quite dim, but food is good.

Nice japanese food street having lot variety of food, ample space to seat dining in.
Suitable for family and friends.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
**update : 2nd visit following last week‚Äôs. That‚Äôs how good the food was. Ambience is nice and chill. This time, I rem go take pic of the meat platter.

Service is good. Eric & team are friendly and very easy going.

Price : $28.80 for a meat platter for 2.

Food quality : fresh and big serving of meat. We had to push each other to finish them

Location : a lil isolated. But if u drive, it‚Äôs easy to find parking spots and it‚Äôs free. I think there are buses on the main road. Not too far in to walk
Food is terrible. waiting 1.5hr only server 2 out of 8 dishes my kids are hungry. this restaurant put coriander in the sharkfin soup ruin the taste. pepper shaker also doesn‚Äôt work. upsetting.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Excellent authentic Indian food and service.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: We have tried ayam talibang, chicken wing nasi lemak, twice at Yishun Park, once at tampines... All Met our expectation  well.  The rice exceeds many stalls we have been over the years. Please keep up and maintain the standards.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Good and prompt service. They have a digital queue system so you can get a number first and they will ring you when ready. Very convenient and great innovation to handle during peak hours.

food is good but only 3 stars because there is a young waitress who served my table that was very unprofessional and rude. She served and push a hot bowl to my table that ÁÉ´Âà∞ my hand but she just walked away üòì when serving it, she didn‚Äôt even say excuse me to inform us she was placing the hot bowl down.   (also she also wears a really short denim shorts while working????)

The lor mee was nice as described. Never order drinks from there especially Milo and coffee. My children ordered Milo and I saw the staff making out from 3in 1 packet and it was very diluted. The staff told me that the coffee was from the coffee machine and hence I didn't order. But she didn't tell with regards to the Milo. I should have guessed.
On 10 Aug 2022 12.20pm buy mian Huey kuih stall the lady attitude rude

The Thai food is pretty authentic and ingredients used quite resemble those found in Thailand. Tried the green curry and soft shell crab with curry. Good range of items on the menu. Staff service is decent. Prices are on the high side, but food quality is pretty good  as

The service here is good and that there were a lot of seats available when I come to have my dinner. The food taste amazing and that it is delivered very quickly through the use of the train set they have. The ordering of food is done through scanning a QR code and ordering at the website. The food is prepared quickly and I had an very good time here.  Would recommend for the residents of Boon Lay to visit and try out their food. Through the food might be expensive for some people though.
Slightly overpriced for what it is... we had chicken curry mee siam which wasn‚Äôt bad but the portion was miserable.

Not sure why the Malaysia Boleh Fried Oyster no longer has the special Penang Fried Oyster taste. It's still good, but it taste like our regular local Fried Oyster. I miss their Penang flavored! Chendol still as good!
There are table and seats at this outlet

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
Both orders were take away.

The first time I ordered a whole chicken I thought it was my imagination that one drumstick was missing.
Ordered a whole chicken again today, my husband who is taller saw the staff place a drumstick and part of the breast back on the counter.
When we went back I checked and there was only one drumstick.

Very dishonest. I will be boycotting this store.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Very yummy jjajang myeon and jjampong. The tang soo yuk and fried mandu were the best I've tasted in Singapore. Will definitely be back for more.

Comforting Thai-inspired fare within Toa Payoh‚Äôs neighbourhood. My favourite was the pork slices ($10), which my friend and I swallowed down before we could take a picture. That, along with green curry chicken, broccoli, Tom yum soup, fish, red ruby, and mango sticky rice, cost us only $30 each! The fish was on promotion though ($12.90 instead of the U.P $22.90). Staff were pretty friendly too!
Be there twice. Food is just ok. Not aware can use their promotion tab via online menu. Order same dish but like 10 dollar more cash. Unable to refund back.

no more xiao long bao :(

- skewers were nice but quite pricey. also the seasoning they use is the same, just the veggie is different. seasoning is VERY salty.
- chives & egg: looks totally different from the menu. portion is huge. no chives taste.
- la zi ji (Ëæ£Â≠êÈ∏°) is fried popcorn chicken kind. so-so, i wouldn‚Äôt buy it again
- È•∫Â≠ê is not bad, q big. $8 for 12

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
Reached at 8pm for our buffet, waited for almost 40min for the first snacks to be served. Chicken cutlet was served FROZEN. After almost 2 hours of waiting and they informed that they were closing, we decided to just forget about those dishes that weren't served yet.
The waiting time super SUPER long (we met a group of friends who were there at 6pm and by 9 they still got couple of dishes tat werent out yet), to make things worst, the pork and mussles weren't even fresh.
Drinks were not included in the buffet price so their strategy could be to drag time and make you order rounds and rounds of drinks and they won't even serve you all the dishes you ordered.
Absolute waste of time, you can get better tasting food at most hawker or Thai restaurants, we ended up paying $45 per pax and got full on drinking water.
Mutton Biryani is very tasty. I was lucky, didnt experience bad attitude or bad service. Ordered from the nice Indian man who was managing the food.

Order food for non spicy for kids, but all food come with chili in it.

Told them that there are chili in the dish, they just took out the chili and reserve the dish again.

Very dishonest and dirty of the restaurant to re-serving the food.
Came here was expecting good Prata but alittle disappointed. Curry also tasted quite weird and you have to scoop it yourself which doesn't make sense also in terms.of hygiene.

Nice little ÁÖÆÁÇí, air-conditioned, neat and clean. We had deep fried squid, tofu and broccoli. The prices may be steeped compared to coffee-shop prices but I think it is worthwhile as it is after all air-conditioned. I like it that the food isn't salty or taste like msg. The tofu was soft on the inside and crispy on the outside. As I don't eat pork, I simply scrapped the pork toppings from the tofu. I appreciate that the waitress is service-oriented. She was attentive and the food were served very promptly. Oh yes, their barley was homemade without the canned drink type of taste. We'll definitely be back!

Food is decent, albeit on the pricier side. Students and staff get 10% off the food.

I got the masala thosai, which was extremely flavourful and tasty. Dhal and chutney provided were rich and flavourful.

The staff was friendly as well, contrary to other reviews. Will consider patronising again if in the area!

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Zichar style but Food was really unique and good! Nice vibe to chill with family and friends. Beer tower is not the cheapest. The staff were attentive and friendly too! There are also many small bites options if you just want to chill there with beer after dinner. My favourite are the fried baby squid and fish roe seafood fried rice (served in stone pot).

The cafe is very Instagramable , it‚Äôs nice for chill out n photo n meeting up with friends , beer r very affordable price .
Owners r friendly couple
Chicken is too small portion size can be improved, maybe add more vege to make it feel more worth it , we prefer smth that is bigger portion. Coffee is a little bitter , can be improved.
The English breakfast cauliflower is not really fantastic, it will be better if u can change it to mash potatoes or sweet corn or potatoes salad . The bread is too thin n small it will be better if u guys can change to a thicker one . Taste wise is perfect . Like a 4 star restaurant. Thumbs up owner .

Went for the $88 pp CNY Lunch, at first they asked us to come earlier even though they had a booking slot for 2pm available on Chope, then when we got there, they were rushing dishes out so as to get us out of the restaurant ASAP. Together with the horrible customer service from the lady manager where she was rude, aggressive and unwilling to serve us, the lo hei/ yu sheng ended up giving the entire family food poisoning! I would honestly, not recommend anyone go back for their CNY Lunch or Dinner services if this is how they treat their customers on Chinese New Year
Nice & clean place for a teh tarik. Staff very pleasant. Worth another visit to try tthe food.
Ok..

Please educate your staff. He refused us to dine in explaining that only fully vaccinated can dine in. There was two of us who had both recieved our 2nd dose 3 days ago, we had our proofs yet he wont let us dine.
Good standard has dropped a lot.  Indian lady cashier was rude and discriminatory. Bring your money elsewhere.
Ordered chicken maggie goreng, indicate in the menu $4.50. In the end, chicken maggie goreng for $8 (chicken thigh with Maggie). The Maggie is salty and it is overprice.

Nice fried rice, not too oily and won't feel jelak.
Ordered pork chop fried rice delivery and it was packed separately from the rice.

Saw lots of reviews and was excited about this being my 1st mee rebus experience. And maybe I just don't like mee rebus but not what I was expecting. The sauce was good and chicken was good. Satay sauce was great unfortunately they didn't start selling satay yet. Maybe I don't know but it seems like this gravy would be better on maybe something besides noodles? Not sure but didn't seem to go well together.  Flavorful but disappointing.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Good

I hv to say the boss is friendly n attentive. The restaurant is small n a little warm. The food is okie. If u r staying ard tt area ya I think it‚Äôs a good place to go if u r craving for Xiao long Bao.
Nice food great service
Ok. The food taste is not bad.

We ordered the jjm, dumplings, seafood stew and the must-order sweet n sour pork.

The pork was a little expensive given the portion (had alot more veggie/onions so the plate itself looks quite full). Dumplings and jjm were average to me. Pretty decent seafood stew but again too much onions for my liking.
Your green chilli chicken damn sedap. I love patronising ur stall

Standard dropped after the son took over and prices are super high now.
Not recommended.

Repeated customer. Tried their festive menu and it was soo worth it. Tasted great too ‚ò∫Ô∏è and their icecream scoops were actually unassumingly nice
Minus 1 star because the service was sooo slow

Haven‚Äôt been to this place for a long time! But during the first time trying out at this outlet, the food was really delicious! The restaurant is very spacious! Must try for the Rosti! Rosti is actually a type of potato that is baked. A bit like prata though. I also like the sausage that came with the Rosti. It is curled like a snail shape. I even liked the beverages served in the menu.

It has been a long since I was last here and the food seems to have gotten better, at least in my experience. Forgot to take pics of the other items we had but the steak was great! Love it that it's served on a hot plate and the steak was not too tough even though we had it medium. Bill came up to $194 for 7 pax with a 1-for-1 main course set.
I love their  prata and tea very  nice
Very nice food, price reasonable and cosy atmosphere. Highly recommend

Went with my date to there for dinner. I think the portion for the don is a bit small and quite pricey and there was no serviette. The wet tissue was chargeable though. Service was ok.

I gave it 4 stars since the don was actually quite tasty. Hope they can improve for those stated above.
Delicious!
Homely and affordable. Reached at about 1+ close to 2pm and they still allowed us to order even though they close at 2.30pm. Can change udon to buckwheat noodles. Also called Sanpachiro

I was not aware of this restaurant and it impressed me! Quite a varieties of soup base, I chose the sze chuan spicy and the other was pork soup.. lovely soup! Ingredients were fresh and at the sauces station, fried garlic was something I like! Refillable of certain beverages was via a constant walk around from the server.. empty plates are cleared promptly so that we have more table space! Pig skin and dace fishball was my fave!

20200816: VERY SNEAKY. Put a side dish say for u and at the end charge u in the bill.
It could have been a gd constant rating for such a top brand restaurant.

Quality of the food is good. Mid tier price range.

Veru doughy and thick skin for both xlb and jian bao. Feels like eating dough instead of the actualt dish. The vinegar condiments given was diluted with some other liquid which makes it not go well with the jian bao and xlb
Price very high but quality very low. Worst experience ever had. Must avoid food stall
Food is not bad. Price can be cheaper.
The chicken dish used to be much better and rice is a little too starchy. The classic deep fried soft tofu still as good as ever. Still good overall.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Great food. Very polite and attentive wait staff even when it's full house. Must try their orh-nee (yam paste dessert), braised duck with tofu and ngoh hiang (superb on its own or with the plum sauce). I don't usually fancy fish dishes but theirs is so fresh! Highly recommended.
Being here few rounds for some dinner. Serving size was good. Food is good too.

I made a reservation via Chope, was happy there was a follow up automated call to confirm the booking & I had specifically state i need the coolest seat available yet when we turn up they told us 'reservation' seat are all alfresco seats & we have to wait till the diners indoor are done. What was not acceptable was no table was set up ready for us at their alfresco area despite telling us 'reservation' is outdoor. If you cannot afford to take reservation, DON'T. I don't see any customer service provided. Totally disappointed & left since the they prefer to entertain walk ins.
Not a place to eat North Indian food.  limited options that too very expensive and below par taste. they don't have price menu and they charged more then what they told me before I started eating.
nothing special for the price tag, and they charge GST separately. small portion, only 4 small slices of grouper fish for $12.8, and instant coffee for $2.3 is a bit ridiculous.
Frustrating experience where they kept screwing up the order. Taking very long

Nice food with friendly Boss and staffs.... avoid weekend or lunch time to have peaceful Teh Tarik. Prata, Thosei and Beryani is delicious even the Beryani rice is lesser than other Beryani seller. Highly recommended for food and service. And I'm a regular for their Teh tarik and beryani :-)
Good food and fair price
Best quality Prata in Ang Mo Kio. Go for it
Finally I find a nice pasta shop inside the school. The pasta is nice and the waiting time is short.

Great place to hangout with friends, however it can be very pack during peak period especially during lunch hour. Best to avoid during this period, if not you can do mobile app via using mcdonald app.
Alternative place to find Filipino food. Ambiance is good. The food choices are limited but enough to satisfy your cravings for Filipino food.
Good quality prata like all their outlets.
Cheesy Chicken Chop is top notch.

We had a nice meal at Curry Times at Novena Square last week after our appointment. This is a retro theme cafe with good variety of local food.
The place is spacious and clean with good safe distancing measures in place .
We enjoyed our sapid nasi lemak with chicken wing and curry chicken. The food was appetising and the curry tasted great to our liking. The only disappointment was the very long wait to be served with our food after placing order .

Yucks! Fried w yellow curry powder.
Took a long time to get the food after chasing !!!
They cannot cope with large volumes.
Never again.
Very unsatisfying.

Extremely tasty Sichuan dishes üôå Service was A+ too, the kitchen missed our order out, and compensated by giving us a free dish! Food is very affordable for the quality, WILL DEFINITELY COME BACK AGAIN :) Â•ΩÂêÉ!
All good tried tasted not bad- char kway teow, prawn mee and chendol. Staff auntie was quite attentive. Ok to visit again.

Was brought to this restaurant by one friend who said that his family will always eat here when visiting at Singapore.

Their roti prata are made fresh to order and thus, what can go wrong with freshly made prata. The curry complemented the prata well. Not expensive at all considering the air con environment.

Had a reservation for a birthday celebration. Food was great! The drinks were expensive but felt that it was worth the experience and turned out to be great. Got a couple of complimentary items too, most likely due to the birthday reservation (Malayan wings and put piring cake). Upon payment, got an additional 2 complimentary cakes (ondeh ondeh and put piring) to bring home, not too sure why though but loving the freebies üòÅ

Though service can be slow when it gets crowded (hence the 4 stars), the ambience was great for the occasion. Overall, will definitely be back for more special occasions.
Fast, efficient service and food that is value for money. Love getting the breakfast sets with ciabatta bread.
Good food, good price
Authentic Shanghai Family style dishes. Must try in AMK

Went Lao Beijing to celebrate my father‚Äôs birthday and was pleasantly surprised by the food quality. Despite the pricing is not that of a high-end Chinese restaurant, the food is definitely top notch. The Peking duck is flavourful and crispy, and the other dishes were also delicious too. Not forgetting the manager- Emily who has prompt and good service. She is efficient, polite and helpful. I will not hesitate to return for meals.
The service is good and food is quality. Great for family. The restaurant is really thoughtful to allocate us with a room for the big group ‚ù§Ô∏è

Only tried the yakitori stall, ok food

Will try other stalls in future

Overall, nothing much changed for ambience, except the name and maybe, owners?

More additions for other shops along the street ba...
Superb service from a friendly uncle with specs. I wish I can award him best employee award.

It‚Äôs been an hour since i placed my order for delivery and even the delivery guy waited at the restaurant for more than half an hour‚Ä¶ the restaurant is STILL preparing and pushing back the delivery time. Assuming it is expedited right as I type this review, it would have reached me more than 90min since I placed the order. When my delivery arrive, the delivery man also say it wasn‚Äôt busy and they must have missed out the order. Yet they denied. Worst late night meal ever. Avoid ordering at all cost!

The foods are bad as what we expected. Actually went over on Monday to try at Jurong outlet. Those meats (pork n beef) Wagyu are totally worst disappointment in meat quality n even a rice are over wet. Terrible Monday dinner.. Please have quality check on food
Service are not to standard, bring to our table yet no one came take order as one of us need to walk out to ask waiter to come over... Is it meant when we seat far away then none will come to take care of our order?

Really oily but the È∫ªËæ£was really there. You have to wait for quite some time for your food (we waited 30min~). Pricing is by grams so it‚Äôll be the same price regardless of meat/vegetables. Ngl the price was a bit more $$ compared to other places‚Ä¶ Milk tea was a bit too sweet but provides a good relief after the spiceüëç

This Chinese food stall tucked in the extreme corner of the food court serves really good food! I had the salted egg pork rice for $6 and it was delicious! The salted egg gravy was thick and flavourful, and the pork nuggets were scrunchy and chewy.

Authentic Ipoh style cuisine. Easy on the pocket.

Review revised on 11 Nov 20.

Now the business here has improved dramatically but service quality went the opposite direction.

The first batch of the staff were from Malaysia. They were humble and very attentive. All left now, possibly due to covid.

The current workers are from China and Vietnam. They have one thing in common: very rude. Especially the China national, just need to sit in here for 5 minutes, you can hear her yelling at customers telling them to collect the food, order verification etc. She even told customers that :"last time no customers, now I am very busy."

The only good service you will receive is from the bosses who appear usually on Sunday.

I hope that they can hire locals or possibly pay more to the staff so that there might be a small chance they would behave better.
Fantastic value for money, well executed dishes. When ordering the beef hor fun, order the small portion for better wok hei. You can read the recommendations on the walls of the outlet

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Love the Indian food here, nice and value for money.
The food is yummy and authentic. They have healthier choice like brown rice. Good to know they don't use MSG

Curiosity cause me to visit this newly opened self serve quick grill establishment. Quite a refreshing alternative to the pepper lunch outlet above.

Recommend to come early as I did before lunch or dinner hour as queue is norm. I selected the sukiyaki karubi set and it was delicious üòã.

The secret is in the marinate and the quick sear cooking that locks in the flavors while maintaining the tenderness of the beef which pairs well with the soy garlic sauce and the onsen egg ü•ö.

Comparatively value for money especially if you compare between other meat based offerings.
Will come back again.. üòÑ

Extremely good service and very satisfied with the food. Very tasty and presented well! Perfect location to host family gathering and celebrations! Speed of serving the food and replenishing the tea is amazing as well. Highly recommended!

Delicious Western food within the Kim Keat Palm Food Centre. Pork Chop came with fries, coleslaw and baked beans. Pork chop itself was tender and tasty. Chicken wings were well marinated and fried to perfection with golden crispy skin. Staff was bubbly and friendly. Fast and efficient services rendered.

Food reminds me of airplane food. It was a unpleasant experience.

Edit: original post from 1 week ago. Shocked to see that there are 5 stars review. Those must be fake. The food is expensive and it does not taste good. Furthermore, the service is bad. When I am there for the first time, I did not notice that I have to order online and I stood there for a long time and the staff simply ignore you. The food is oily, the croissant I had was cold. Please try for yourself to find out the truth.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: The wait times are horrible. I am waiting for more than an hour when the restaurant is only 25% full. Please check the wait times before you order here.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The little old lady serving us is such a sweetheart!! Decent food. Took a long time to have our orders taken and seated though.
Very decently price steak and food is amazing. Decent potion. Wings and steak is a must try!

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: We order lunch from here about once every 2 weeks and everyone loves it. The spiciness is just right and well the taste is as best it can get.
Great Indian food, mee / Maggi goreng is good. Rice set, especially with mutton, is amazing. YMMV

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Clearly the food here is pretty good, especially the fish soup bee Hoon. The other dishes such as Thai tofu is nice as well. Downside of the place is that the seating comfort is pretty poor. And staff service is just simply atrocious, rude and unwelcoming. And food serving just takes such a long time despite the place being quite empty.

Very AUTHENTIC Shanghainese taste. The quality is good. The first on the pan fried bun... Oh gosh! The meat 'gravy' in the bun just ooze out. You cannot just eat it with chopsticks. You need a spoon while eating the bun. As for the 'gravy' that ooze out on the spoon, well. Drink them! It is not oily and it is clear. VVFM. (Very Valued For Money)

Will give four stars coz hope they will continue to maintain their standard and strive to better.
Nice family style restaurant. Great lunch deal and beef is from NZ! Portion size is good.

Waited 30 mins in line and they had only move 7 people. Slow service because they committed to a massive pre order they couldn‚Äôt keep up with. After each customer they would have to pack 5 packs for the pre order. Worst experience.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Their Char Siew is fantastic!

Had an excellent lunch at the newly revamped Lao Beijing. The service staff were very polite and attentive. The Peking Duck is even better than the version we had at the old place. Highly recommended!

Now with the pandemic and looking where to bring my parent for dinner? I know my parent will love this traditional chinese restaurant since their relocation from Bukit Merah to Newton. I didn't know until my parent told me Happy Joy almost 40 years in the market! Comfortable dining as tables are spread a distance away and don't feel crowded. I called to make reservation and understand that their buffet dinner at $39.80 per pax, promo 4 free 1 promotion until end of June. It's an absolute steal for this price! I will be back soon.
What can we ask for with this price that includes peking duck, abalones, shark fin, superior treasure pot, soon hock fish and more...Great food, great price and indeed great nice people in the restaurant.

The staff is helpful and sent me their set menu with mini birthday buns, I will be back for my dad 70th birthday!
Ordered  a tomahawk pork steak,  a bit of char but just nice to me! Crispy  and juicy , reasonable  price and huge portion üëçüèª strongly recommend

ÁèçÂë≥

Wanted to try a nearby Thai cuisine but it was not opened yet.

We then settled for this zichar stall at another coffee shop.  The white beehoon (ÁôΩÁ±≥Á≤â@S$5.50) and san lou hefen (‰∏âÊçûÊ≤≥Á≤â@S$5.50) were not too bad, better than expected.  The serving of white beehoon was quite big.

You may want to give it a try if you are around here, and run out of idea on what to eat.
Very cozy and pleasant place. Very friendly staff. Special mention to the beautiful and sweet singer from KL  and her guitarist from Manila, kababayan... sorry forgot to get their names.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Excellent Teochew cruisine, arguably the best in sg.  Tried a variety of their signature dishes and the sea cucumber, crispy on the outside and soft inside really stands out.
Really Authentic, generous portion, value for money, can't get enough of it!

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content:
Worst service ever.. If u guys planing to buy food via grab. Just forget it, no matter hw many times u order always gt missing items.
They always will forget to give important items.

I have experience 3 to 4 times

Buy idli they forget to give chutney and curry.

Buy vegetarian briyani and tauhu sambal.
They forget to give briyani.

Ridiculous.

If you stayed or studied around Ang Mo Kio Central area, you should be familiar with Rasa Sayang Western Food that‚Äôs located at the S-11 coffeeshop next to Jubilee Square

A few years ago, the stall was taken over by a group of young owners, and well, the standards dropped drastically.

I‚Äôm really excited that the original owners have reopened at a coffee shop opposite AMK Hub, about 10-15 minutes‚Äô walk away!

While most people ordered their value-for-money chicken cutlet, I ordered their Chicken Chop ($6.50) which is probably one of the best old school Hainanese western food I‚Äôve ever eaten.

While the sides like fries, baked beans and even the slice of garlic bread is nothing exciting, the star of the dish is their mushroom sauce.

Perfectly balanced, not overly salty, with hints of chicken stock and slices of soft button mushrooms, this sauce makes the long queue worth it.

Chicken was grilled well and lightly charred to add a layer of smokiness that compliments the sauce.

P.S. Don‚Äôt waste the sauce, use the fries to scoop up every bit of it! üòã

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Food and price are reasonably good..

This is my third time to attend her cooking classes.  This time is the Chicken Xiao Long Bao.  It is awesome and the Chef Payal is the Best.  Her class is well organized and I learnt a lot from making the chicken stock to how to make dumplings. Of course, the Xiao Long Bao is seriously delicious and juicy! Highly highly recommended her cooking classes to everyone!  üëç

Was excited to try their mee rebus after watching Chef Bob‚Äôs review but was unpleasantly surprised by the uncle‚Äôs rudeness. We came at 1130am and asked if there is still mee rebus, we didn‚Äôt know that they only open at 1230noon. To our dismay, he answered us rudely by saying ‚Äúcan‚Äôt you see we are preparing?‚Äù We don‚Äôt stay around there, so we don‚Äôt know the area well. We don‚Äôt need 5 star treatment, just be polite. Even though we never had the chance to try the food, I will never come back. I don‚Äôt owe you a living to be treated that way.

Popped by for lunch after seeing the reviews online. Fish balls were nice and bouncy and noodles were good! Decently priced at $4.

It was sold out by 12:44pm so my recommendation is get there early!

I was there for dinner with a few friends and we had a great experience eating there! They were patient with us as we ordered multiple times because we wanted to try more food.

We loved the Chicken 65 and Mutton dishes üôå

Even though we stayed closed to closing, they were very patient in waiting for us to finish. Appreciate the service and standard of food!!

Quick friendly service. Food is good. Physical menu and we order by writing on the order chit. Located near one of the level 1 entrances in JEM. There is outdoor seating as well. As the place gets its air conditioning from the central air conditioning, it can be a bit warm at certain seats on a hot afternoon. Payment at the counter when we exit.

It‚Äôs a bit below expectations based on the other strong reviews. Aglio olio was dished together with the chicken that came with a cream sauce - hmm? Pork belly was dry and the sweet sauce didn‚Äôt help to ease the flavor. There was nothing garlicy about the fries and it was rather salty. Egg was on point. I supposed the salad in garden greens would compliment the dish better.
Ordered delivery for dinner, and food quality was as good as dining in. Highly recommended üëçüèª
Crab is super big and at affordable price. Kian Seng is also super generous with the chilli crab sauce as can be seen from photo. Will totally come back again for more!

If you're a fan of spicy food, this place will satisfy--unfortunately for us, even when we specified one of our dishes to have no spice, the dish was still overbearingly spicy! Our suspicion is that they cooked our spicy food (the mee goreng and maggi goreng) in the wok first, then cooked the nasi goreng, which was meant to be partially fed to a toddler.

Nicely decorated in an industrial theme aptly because this is located in an industrial building. Huge variety of beer and drinks at an affordable price. Great for large gatherings and family dinners. Good array of other eateries in the same food court. Parking could be challenging though. Advice to come outside of peak period to avoid the massive crowd during lunch.
Good range, food quality , ambience were ok. But nothing is really memorable and making me want to come back again. Think it‚Äôs a little overpriced.

After so many years, silkroad has managed to maintain its standard. The Peking duck was crispy on the outside and moist on the inside. Superb!

Dec 2021 - Nth time at silk road
Tried the cod for the first time. Not bad. Smooth. Will try again

Dec 2021 (again!) - scallops asparagus not as spicy as I hoped for but still good. Wasabi prawn with potato crisps were great! Half chicken was juicy and not dry. Love.

The restaurant was packed, probably the reason why 1 of the staff was disgruntled.. she slammed our drinks on the table & was a little rude.
The dishes were delicious.
Great food although at a slightly higher price point. Servers were helpful and accommodating to our requests.

Great place for prata. The Tissue Prata was really thin and crispy. They serve crispy type prata. The egg onion prata is delicious too.
We were first given chicken curry, and when we asked for a refill, were served fish curry. Both were flavourful and yummy.
It gets crowded, and there's not a lot of parking available. Go during off peak hours or travel by public transport.

Be prepared to wait for at least an hour to get a seat as it is very popular n the restaurant is quite small.  But it is worth the wait as the dishes r unique n delicious.  We ordered fried sweet yam n steam mee sua which r üòã There r many more dishes that must try eg herbal prawn in bamboo stick, lychee pork, etc...
The chicken is hard as well as the prata . Did not enjoy food after trying a few more times.

The service staff here are very friendly and food is slightly cheaper than outside. Otherwise there is still a lunch crowd but surprisingly wait times are not unreasonable

Pretty good place
Best place for a great bowl of fish soup... yummy tze char too
Very nice yakiniku. Fast service and delicious. This outlet is self service model, which I think speed up the overall dining time.
The vegetarian food served here is great. Besides food, I like their Masala tea and coffee. In addition to food and drinks, the customer service is good as well.

Chance upon Sushi Go while exploring B1 of  Jurong Point. The main question to answer is Genki Sushi vs. Sushi-Go. It was almost a year since i been to Genki but i felt the variety of sushi was more in Sushi Go. The online menu through scanning the QR is user friendly but it would be nice to see what order has been served through the app. Every $20 for a token to ice cream claw machine although it is not 100%. However one small issue is that they serve powder for the hot green tea instead of tea bags so after the first cup most of the tea is gone.
Traditional Zhi Cha at an industrial area coffee shop. Huge space and the food are good but no air-con.

Located at #03-05 of the mall.
Not that crowded even during holiday.
Wide range of options for the soup base, do take note that each person was expected to have an individual pot. The staff did mention that even if 2 people wished to share a pot, it was alright.
The food as fresh and the quantity was sufficient. The price was still considered reasonable.
The service was alright, but to compare with other hotpot restaurants, clearly it was lacking.

The joke was, one staff couldn‚Äôt even recognise me when I stood at the entrance after my meal. She still asked me if I wanted to go in to have a meal. And after I told her, that I just had a meal inside. She gave me the weird look.
Probably the best Karaage I had so far in Singapore. Price point is very reasonable and every dish was great. Seasoning was on point too. Great selection of sake. Will definitely come back

Food was decent,  variety ok. Prices subjected to 10% svc charge but quite reasonable. We told the person is our first time, and they patiently explained the menu items and how to order. Also came by to check if we needed soup refill. Would love to come by indulge once in a while. Also quite nice on. Weekday is not crowded and they did not rush us to leave after eating.
We tried the CNY menu here and found the dishes very delicious. The chef combine chinese cooking from different region of china. From fish to roast chicken , surpringly good and yummy.
Hands down one of the best Thai Ice Cream I have ever had. Good variety with unique combinations that will surely be a must to try for anyone who visits this place.
one of the best beef noodles in sg

Beef noodle with very tiny beef
cannot believe there is no spring onion for Ëë±Ê≤πÈù¢ & fried buns ü•≤
Maybe the dumplings & spring roll are the best, but I won‚Äôt come again.
you may avoid ordering noodles.

Here‚Äôs my bang-for-buck ratings

Food: 4/5
Service: 3/5
Price: 3/5
Decor & seating: 3/5

Highly recommend stewed beef cubes. Grilled salmon a tad too salty.
Unagi sushi was not bad.
Swordfish belly was on point based on taste and texture.
Momo peach ice cream was yucks.
Sesame ice cream passable.

Service was so-so, not proactive which means tea pretty much unfilled and finished dishes not cleared promptly. Fortunately staff still attended upon request.

Ordered chicken chop with butter rice through food panda. Requested for more sauce and fries. To my very pleasant surprise the boss was very generous to my request. Of cos the food is delicious as well. Pricing is affordable too. Will recommend anyone who craves for western food to visit them.
Ps:the butter rice is super delicious
For those who love to eat very sweet mee rebus, then this is the one.  The satay sauce topping was even sweeter than the rebus gravy.
Fish not ready during lunch hour, person taking orders very unclear with his communication.

The ramen taste is not bad for chicken based broth. Ordered the Ichikokudo extra rich Ramen and it came with shredded fish and chicken chasu. Ordered big fry ebi don too but it was disappointing. The rice came in big clumps and is super wet and sticky. Ebi fry is not crispy at all and super soft, like mochi texture. The egg contained prawns as well, too much for my preference but seafood lovers might like it? Gyoza skin is slightly thick and made using chicken as well, no dipping sauce was provided. The set comes with fruits not drinks so drinks have to be order d separately but green tea is refillable. Overall would not order the don again unless improvement is made to the rice and ebi fry. This place is Halal as well so an additional option for halal friends to dine at.
Good price for big portions.
Good quality, delicious Nasi Lemak discovered here in this coffeeshop. Love at first bite. Must try. There's always queue here.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: In totally in love with this place and ambience. The Tamil song which they play welcomes you to the bar! On the other hand their food varieties are awesome. Their Grilled chicken and Garlic naan is our favourite dish of them. They also have bar facilities. Do check them out. Authentic and amazing. Highly recommend

Chicken katsu don very underrated ‚Äî best I've ever had!!
Mentai sauce is also extremely good! :)
One of my all time favourite restaurant. Really good food at very reasonable prices. The helpings are generous and everyone in the family loves the food!
No fries came with the fish and chips that I ordered. The mashed potatoes were quite good, but everything else was adequate at best.
OK food, worse attitude from the guy on duty at night. Used to be decent.
During my recent visit, I find their sambal and coconut rice standard are not as good compared to when they start up.
Quality of food is good. Nice for supper . Slightly expensive

Saw this a week before when me and my partner was on our way to sembawang hot spring water and my partner did his research and brought me here today to surprise me.. Loved the food which tasted like home cooked food.. My partner wanted bitter gourd 65 but unfortunately the vegetable wasn't available nevertheless he ordered cauliflower 65 and finished the whole serving by himself. The highlight was the "Price" which definitely not expensive as other restaurants. We both was full the whole day until we skipped our dinner.. Thumbs up üëçüëçüëçüëç

Good measure of social distancing with tables well spaced out. We tried the breaded fish & chips and lamb chops which were nice. Cream cake on sale near the counters are old school styled.

They ran out of mango gelato which perhaps can be managed if stocks are planned earlier in advance because ice cream usually have a longer shelf life
Delicious curry puff and breakfast menu, quick service

We came for lunch on a weekday, it was almost deserted. Some dishes were fairly okay like the roast chicken. There was this salted fish tofu claypot that was quite odd and did not have any salted fish taste or bits.
Ambience is okay. Service could be improved. Some of the seafood or fish pricing seemed high.

Food is really good here! Love the Lor Mee and the Lychee Meat ü§© would like to commend Zhang Lan too! She‚Äôs so nice and friendly, dish she recommended us is really v nice! Nice dinner on mid week, made our day! :)

I find that the nasi lemak standard to differ batch to batch. Sometimes the rice can be abit too wet for my liking. Amazing price for the standard as it is consider affordable. If only the standard can be more consistent will be great.
Worst experience ever! Please do be nice to your customers!
Ordered chicken steak for take away, turned out to be potato masala. More potato and less chicken. Taste was satisfactory and still doesn't know how potato and vegetables end up in a steak!!!

Cozy place for some well cooked and great tasting Thai food. The Chef is Thai.which makes the difference. Its not air con but is airy with good ventilation and fans. Make sure you also get a bottle of iced water!
I spend $14 for 2packets. Ask for more chillies  didnt give and definitely not enough to cover the rice. Will not visit this stall anymore. They are so lousy!!
Non authentic Thai food. It‚Äôs the worst Phad Thai Chicken I have tasted in my life. Lack flavour, bland. The Noodle was under cooked before it was fried. Will not be here again for sure.

Curly fries was over salty. Mixed lamb n fish presentation was lacklustre, piece of fish was small, overall taste still alright. Beef stew and rice tasted nice. Overall good enough for a quick business lunch.

Ordered from them on Grabfood and the food was not packed properly and the sauce spilled all over the bag. Not only so, I‚Äôve topped up $3.80 for popcorn chicken and I received a pathetic little bag of it, on top of the the paper bag that contained the chicken was soaked in oil. I hope the restaurant would consider better packaging and to reconsider their portion sizes for some of their items.

Value for money
Love the grilled chicken and baked potato
Lamp chop is great too
Chicken wings also yummy

When I saw the long queue for this, i knew i had to join in to check it out!

This is "Hi Leskmi" which is quite an unusual name that sells Nasi Lemak.  The stall uses an Indian name, owned by a Chinese guy, selling Malay Food. Talk about Racial Harmony!

Rice itself I feel is not really fragrant, and the Chicken Drumstick itself while Crispy, is nothing special. Sambal Chilli is sweetish. The whole meal however comes together quite well and is very filling. Not really worth queuing up for tbh.
Doesn't really like there. Is quite disturbing. Even the staff would brings up politics views of the company to you. When you already had enough from your work place.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Went for lunch today, waited for the food almost 45 minutes. One of our juice that ordered never came till we finish our lunch and had to take away. Upon reaching the restaurant, though it was crowded due to mother's day, no water served. Looks like they are disorganized. Few who came and just walked out as nobody bothered to serve them. Please improve your service level. Thank you.
Quite authentic Penang type Hokkien mee. Really quite delicious especially the yuan yang. Recommended, serve quite fast too. Will be perfect if the soup can be more generous!

Place to go for Awesome Dosa varieties, Vada, Bajjis and Sweets. Furthermore you get a service with smile and a homely feel. Do try out their Dosa Varieties and if you intend to try their Idlies do plan to reach their outlet by 19:00 PM as it gets finished very fast.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Decent mookata in the neighbourhood, price is affordable, $70+ for 4pax for ala carte. The cheese dip is a must get and the smoked duck too! Free flow ice cream too, the sauces are decent too. A nice place to satisfy ur cravings

Horrible service attitude and lousy food. Google states opening hours till 10pm. When arrived at 7.50-8pm, cook from the fried carrot stall mentioned that the claypot rice stall cook is having his meals rudely. So we ordered the Penang fried kway tiao while we waited. But taste of the CKT was way below average.

After the cook finished his meal, he just informed that his stall is closed! He should just mentioned it‚Äôs closed when we asked about it and we do not need to even order the Penang CKT!! Waste of time.

Place is also dirty with dead cockroach under the table. Horrible cleanliness.

Seriously Fei Siong group should manage the staff better. And UPDATE YOUR OPENING HOURS!!
Thick prawn soup with nice chilli sauce, delicious
Good  variation of food, nice pork noodle and Penang prawn mee. Clay pot rice 's staff are rude.
Prices reasonable staff Malay ladies very friendly fast service
Not bad. Cheese mentaiko potato is a must try. Most of the dish quite decent, price is quite ok.. can try.
Seriously one of the best Thai food in TOA Payoh lor2. Value for money the owner very friendly and helpful and staff
Nice Western food but waiting time always very long
Awesome
Food is always served quickly and its delicious. Rice is tasty, chicken is tender, and chilli is not too spicy but still adds alot of flavour.

Poor service,for take away order waiting more than 40 minutes
Poor food quality
Visit first and last time
Very kampong style, a bit pricey, food is not too bad, if only their prata can be a little bit more crispy.

Google steakhouse at AMK and this place popped up.

Not too bad for a steak within a HBD neighbourhood. We had the ribeye and NY sirloin steak, both were quite good considering the price was very reasonable.

The pull pork burger was equally tasty as well. Moist enough and with the cheese on it, not bad at all.

Onion rings and the affogato were alright. But the French fries were super crispy and it's like McDonald's curly fries except it's not curly üòÇ

If I could give 0 stars, I would. Waited so long for food, orders were messed up (people who came later than us got food first), and the food quality was just sad. Not a single food that was good. Haven't had such a bad meal in such a long time, not to mention one order was missed out (but by then it was more like thank goodness...). Sorry this is a no-go.
It is a very characteristic street. A lot of stores. And some good restaurants. There are also some ninjas sneaking on your heads. And it is always crowded.
Seafood always the best..

Should have read the latest reviews before going. Used to visit this place a lot before its temporary closure. Standard has really dropped. The beef brisket is dry and doesn't taste great. The cheeseburger bun and patty are burnt to  the extent that they leave a bitter after taste. Only the fries is nice. The big guy (not the boss) taking my order doesn't look keen to work there, which is obvious based on how the food turn out. Don't think will come back again unless the quality improves.
Generous and friendly staff. Accommodated my requirement and gave me a free bun :)
Tried the pan fried fish (R3) with mushroom sauce. For the price of 4.8, this is really good with pearl/Japanese rice.
Nice food! The service was good and attentive (ÈùôÈõ™was extremely friendly). Highly recommended!
Relatively costly, but still good enough food.. a monthly treat is ok
Polite cashier who took the order. Nice gravy comes with freshly made dosa. Masala tea is nice unlike some too sweet. Overall v good experience.  Well done, good job!!

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: This... is one of the worst crystal jade I‚Äôve ever eaten at. I could go on and on about how bad the food is. The shanghai nian gao was totally off putting. It looks terrible and tastes worse. It‚Äôs bland, sweet and ugly all at the same time. Jelly fish was too soggy. The promotional item, hainanese xiao long bao tastes like dessert meat. It‚Äôs oh so sweet. The crispy fried beancurd skin was seeping in oil. Drunkard chicken is tough and salty. The har gao is too peppery and beneath the peppery mask is soggy smelly prawns. The worst thing? The damage for all these is $80++
Hot, fresh and crispy prata in a breezy morning. love this branch because the surronding area is so tranquil
Good place, nice food , good Service , thumbs up for the staff there specialy to Miss Inky
Thanks today
First time dinning here. Good and reasonable prices

Went for lunch at the tunglok peking duck outlet at Novena Square today, but the standard of the peking duck is totally no consistency. The peking duck is soooooooo oily!! Paid $98 (havent incl. GST and service charge) for this to drink oil? It is really disappointing!! üò°üò° I got video of it too!!!

Good place for noodles and simple Chinese dishes. Beef noodles is pretty good with noodles having a good texture. Xiao Long Bao and some of the other snacks taste good. The recent afternoon tea ala carte buffet is pretty good too with a nice range of dim sum. Price for the buffet is reasonable.

I've tried their mentaiko chicken, truffle beef yakiniku and their teriyaki chicken and I have never been disappointed. Super generous portions, delicious and very value for money. All have been deliveries so i can't speak for service or ambience but 10/10 for food.
Food was okay, portion sizes were okay. Staff was friendly but the ambience was dull. Not very lively place. Only me was there in the restaurant while other nearby places were kinda crowded.

Sometimes I want to be induced into a food coma. When I need that, this is where I come. Pork burrito does the trick. Eat one and a nap is sure to follow. Puts me to sleep faster than my wife chatting in bed.
Reasonably priced. The briyani chicken i had could be better if the food was warm.

Delicious hotpot with yummy soup! I am always not sure why people prefer Beauty In the Pot over Paradise Hotpot.. It's essentially the same ingredients and somewhat similar soup.

This place is conveniently located at the 3rd story of Compassone. It can get crowded during dinner timings, so be sure to reach before 7pm and claim your seats!

Friendly staff and delicious prata.. the curry is perfect and the prata is crispy..

Keep it up.üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

The teh tarik kosong is smooth too

Very good Mutton Briyani.. the curry is thick and spicy.. the Mutton is very solid üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

Very bad staff attitude. Requested non spicy Char Koay Tiao for my kids but the staff refused to accommodate the request even there was no other customer. Reason being it is a ‚Äústandard‚Äù taste for Msian CKT with chili! The Bak Kut Teh tasted terrible with low quality ingredients. Won‚Äôt go back for sure!

The service is quite excellent. I like that they do not squish the patrons which I like (you don't feel that others watching you eat). The duck has maintained the standard. The boiled soup is rather too salty. The rest of the food is quite average, the portions varies from dish.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Dine in with group of 5 you can order more dishes. Chili crab price consider reasonable at $88. The vermicelli is something different than other zhi char stall and it taste good with all the seafood. They also serve flaming roasted chicken which we skipped this time as we wanted to have prawn. The crispy garlic prawn is so good that you may have the crispy garlic and rice and chili crab sauce on its own. It‚Äôs just so staple. Overall their food are ok, restaurant is clean, it‚Äôs very suitable for gathering. They are not air conditioned but under shade. They also have outdoor table which I was initially have interest on but pull back as it is only cater for smoking zone. How nice if they have some non-smoking outdoor tables which people can eat/drink and enjoy the surroundings openly.

Good food. Excellent service. Nice environment.

Shout out to Daphne who provided outstanding services.

Happy with generous portion salad bowl choice with grilled chicken for lunch. Was able to finished all the food as the salad bowl paired off nicely with grilled chicken and wasabi taste paste. The boss of the stall is friendly too.

Will come back if around link@amk again

#salad bowl #characol #grillchicken #coffeeshop

Truly homely cooked food with the diversity in selection. Never fails to perk up my weekends with the different combination of dishes to try out here.
It has many must try dishes which can only be experienced with multiple visits

I order Grill platter take away with sides: coleslaw and sweet potato fries (had to pay extra $0.50). When I reach home, the set contain all the wrong sides, ie, whipped potato and corn broccoli (both I don‚Äôt eat). Paying extra and not getting what I ordered is really not the main issue. Spoiling my whole dinner experience was really upsetting. This will be the last time I dine with Jws.
30% off ala carte is worth it during weekdays off peak hours. As usual their signature herbal duck satisfies to no end. Match made in heaven with their moist & fluffy white rice.

UNO beef house a long standing brand in the heartlands of Toa Payoh. There‚Äôs a reason why they can survive the test of time - the steaks are reasonably priced and food is good. THE MUST HAVE SIDE IS THE FRIED MASHPOTATO‚Äô non beef eaters you can opt for chicken/lamb/pork
Food was very good, love the experience! Prawn paste chicken was delicious, venison was tender and tasty! Would definitely come again!!
Do check your order before taking away.. they gave the wrong order and the whole bowl no1 eat. What a waste of food.. not everyone loves truffles..
Great place for briyani lovers at the North. The Boss and lady Boss are very friendly and accomodating. A must try!!!

Been a huge fan of this Msian foodcourt at Jurong Point for several years, so glad they have set up one nearer home at AMK HUB, and recently at Simei Eastpoint Mall too.

Apparently it's a foodcourt concept set up by Feixiong, who owns many EATs at shopping mallls. The best is the Penang fried kuayteow, full of wokhei n uses Ipoh stubby bean sprouts, curry chicken beehoon is yummy, more flavourful than HongLim's lemak style. Hokkien prawn noodles and fishballs are great too. Rojak's sauce is very authentic Penang style.

Recently they have added curry chee cheong fun, quite authentic too
Good place to bring your western friend there to dine in !
Attended a wedding dinner here and I enjoyed the entire night. Food is good. Service is nice. I don‚Äôt feel like being rushed. And my wine is always filled without me noticing it. Jia You!

Mee Rebus with a twist, definitely worthwhile to add the poached chicken for just additional one dollar. Though the mee rebus is good in itself, the gravy is a tad overly gooey so the added chicken really help balance out the texture of the whole dish.

Homely family business that serves up amazing food. Uncle mentioned that they only use fresh chicken and coconut for their curry chicken. Definitely could taste the difference. Opens during CNY, will come back again.
Chuan Rong has good service attitude, friendly and on task. Peak performance
Standard Indian-muslim food options. A bit on the oily side. Birds do fly in to the eating areas. Staff could be more proactive in chasing the critters away.

Best xinghua food I've tasted so far. I personally find it better than putien even and priced very well. Ordered delivery thrice in 2 weeks, taste wise standards are high and consistent with good wok-hei, portions were big and delivery wait wasn't too long. Highly recommend!!!
The jajangmyeon tasted a little different from Tae Woo‚Äôs to me, but their sweet & sour pork was much better than Tae Woo‚Äôs.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: One of my favourite eats at this hawker centre (Kalsom Kuih Muih is my other must-visit for their curry puffs). My favourite selections are the ayam taliwang belado and the nasi lemak with everything. The belado comes with a well seasoned, spoon-tender grilled chicken leg. Nice smoky flavours go well with the two chilli sauces, one sweeter one for the coconut rice (not overly lemak) and a spicier, pedas coarsely textured chilli for the chicken. They will pack the chilli separately in individual containers if you need to manage the spicy level.
Many items and soup base to choose from. Paid about $32nett a pax for buffet on weekday. Service was good but can‚Äôt say much about the taste of the food.

Kia Hiang has been around for 30 plus years and its specialties are chicken wrapped in cabbage and braised in a claypot, a dry hotplate toufu that's like a toufu omelette, and bean sprouts with salted fish.
Kia Hiang recently added dim sum to the menumenu
Wonderful dinning environment. Great service crews. After 2 years, it is as great as before.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Always love Aston‚Äôs for their affordable prices n good food. Will always order the steak with a glass of red wine. Now that it has become a halal establishment, no more alcohol is served. Nevertheless, the food is still great at that price.

Ordered the teriyaki salmon don at $5.50. Love that they top the salmon with lots of stir-fries onions and also generous amount of lettuce. Comes with miso soup too. Portion is good too. Gave it 3 star as it didn‚Äôt taste Japanese even though it was a good meal that I enjoyed.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: This is the toa payoh central outlet. Clean, cooling environment, food is well marinated, fresh and tasty, and the service by the Thai waiting staff were warm and awesome. I would recommend that you guy provide tongs to bbq the meat. One can expect to spend around $70++ for 2 pax if you opt for the canned oolong drinks as well. Oh and they use gas instead of charcoal‚Ä¶which tastes slightly different from traditional charcoal mookata but still very good!

All park restaurants have that added charm which is usually offsetted by the premium price.

Toriyard is no exception. Food wise, quality was average, pricing slightly higher which was not unexpected. Service was quite good, pleasant wait staff, common man type rather than those posh places.. attentive and smiley.

Worst thing about the place is the menu. First off, menu was only online and connection was extremely slow. Page took a min each to load. And.... It had no pictures.

So skewer chicken had a difference with grilled chicken... Although, because there wasn't any pictures... I couldn't tell what the differences were. And because there were no pictures, I didn't know what the plating was.

Buckwheat noodles in soup... Could really look very appealing, or go the totally opposite direction and be a huge letdown.

Anyway, all in all, 3/5.

Waited for 30min for a table of 2 on wed night. Some food already out of stock. Had mushroom aglio and buttermilk chicken.
Mushroom aglio is real bad. Tasteless and funghi taste is too heavy. Told the staff about it, she nicely replaced a new one. But it still taste worse than home cook. It‚Äôs $14+ for. Small plate.
Chicken was salty and falling out by bits and pieces. Don‚Äôt wan even need to use knife.
Left. Hungry.

My colleague and I ordered mutton briyani for lunch. The delivery was so prompt. Food was still warm and smelled flavourful. Since the recent days I have been yearning for mutton briyani. Neethe has appeased me with a delectable and a scrumptious meal. I didn‚Äôt expect the mutton to be very tender and too soft. Boneless mutton. Very satisfactory portion and the mutton pieces were more than enough. The cucumber salad was a sweet company along with the briyani and the mutton. It was really value for the money. And not forgetting the boiled egg. Thank you Neethe for providing me with such a heart contented meal. My request is please do not compromise the quality of your food for anything at anytime. Maintain it. If not increase the qualityof the food.

First time trying nasi Padang in this shop, tempted by the crowd. It‚Äôs always full house during lunch. I ordered 2 meats 1 veggie cost me $8.80. I had a slice of fish, squid and ladies fingers with ayam merah gravy and sambal belacan. The spiciness was mild for me. Overall food is average and their sets come with drink but I didn‚Äôt order the set with drinks. They also sell some kuih-muih but didn‚Äôt manage to try their kuih.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Not the best roti John I ate..  e other dishes was ok

Really wonderful food to satisfy even the sharpest of tongues in my family.
I tried almost everything on the menu already and can say..... I'll be back as everything is very well done.
Best part is..... the pricing is so fair and it's a wonder they are not yet on Michelin or Bill Gourmand.... keep up the standard

Environment was clean.
Some hits and misses here for the dishes.

Fried rice with slightly bland. There was some canned luncheon meat, carrots, egg and sliced pork.

The beef hot pot stock was quite salty. The beef was sliced beef. Our guess is they are using frozen beef. When it came, a chunk of them were stuck together and raw when we separated them.
We ate a total of 1 slice. There was also canned luncheon meat.

Cabbage was crunchy and tasty with slight umami. Quite good.

The fried bun with pork was very nice. Slight porky taste. But still bearable if you are not sensitive to it.

So overall I would have to say this isn‚Äôt value for money if you are going for quality of ingredients.
Would be a nice restaurant to pop in if you stay around the area. I‚Äôm quite sure they have other dishes that are tasty. However, this was all I could eat.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Good quality food. Reasonable price. Both veg and non-veg options. Indian snacks available. Nice ambience to sit out. They don't chase you even if you spend quite a long time.

If without Get Great Promotion will not know that nice THAI food hidden in such area.
Prices are reasonable and portion are huge too.
Must try the Papaya Salad and Pork Cheeks.

A must-go place for delicious prata! Must try for their unique prata and their prata curry. Highly recommend Prata Alfredo if you love cheese and the plaster blaster. The salted egg prata is not to my liking, it doesn‚Äôt taste like salted egg.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
THE CUSTOMER SERVICE WAS REALLY AWFUL. WE HAD TO WAIT FOR 20 MINS EVEN THOUGH IT WAS NOT A RUSH THAT DAY. THE FOOD ITEMS WERE UNDERCOOKED.
I RECCOMEND U GUYS NOT TO EVEN COME NEAR THIS RESTAURANT

My favourite place for crab tang hoon!! Crab us very fresh and often the meat at the legs are firm and juicy.. no kid. The tang hoon is cooked nicely with right amount of sauce firmness and yummy til the bottom of the clay pot.. if you know what I mean. The variety is plentiful and often a place for mid price family gatherings etc as they also serve roasted whole pig which they do themselves.. we also like the pork or fish sweet and sour since seperate.. parking is relatively easy too and on weekends they have valet..  enjoy.
Very tasty San Lao Hor Fun and beautifully fried plate of fibre and crispy hae bee.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Very nice Indian foods with reasonable price. Good Ambient too.
Accessible everyday food
lovely place with great music and great vibes!!!! nice service too!!

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: This one taste good like real chicken soup without me boiling few hrs. Convenient and easy to prepare..
Portion size abit small but is delicious
Cleanliness and hygiene need improvement
$4.50 for chicken chop, very affordable

Don't listen to the five star review below by the accounts that looks like they were purposely created just to give a single review for this restaurant (two accounts, five star, one review only.. really?). food is inconsistent. prices are downtown japanese restaurant prices. Had the rice bowl , came with HARD BOILED EGG. R u kidding me? Rejected and demanded onsen egg as advertised on the menu. Took them 20 minutes and to my dismay , they served me a SOFT BOILED EGG (a.k.a kopitiam breakfast egg). And for 9.90++, no Miso soup? Service isn't great also (no one speaks English, so good luck if you're a foreigner or Japanese and can't speak mandarin). Why charge service charge then? Been here a couple of times, been disappointed every time. Once, we ordered 3 type sashimi and they substituted maguro with salmon (they ran out of maguro), however the price remains the same. The kitchen staff kept glaring at me today for inconveniencing them by demanding the onsen egg. Hello!!!? Isn't it your job to prepare the dish according to the menu? I'm just amazed a supposedly JAPANESE food stall tried to nonchalantly pass off their rice bowl with a hard boiled egg (and they did it to several customers)! You'd be better off having the rice bowl at kopi&tarts further down the linkway - at least they serve the correct type of egg, and it's cheaper too.
Love the chicken chop here! Come try it yourself.
Cockroach in the beef glass noodle that I ordered last night. Totally gross and threw away all other food that I have ordered. No hygiene at all. Avoid at all cost!
One of the best, pssss Google asked for second review?
Had an enjoyable dining experience at this newly renovated outlet. Interesting and delicious dishes. Attentive service from the crew, with Emily leading the team.

Food so so. Considering the location and old rundown condition of the place , price is high. They run out of char siew but didn't mentioned until serving the ramen, simply replaced with chicken with an take it or leave it attitude. No more repeat visit...
Their steaks are always the best among it's price range

Newly opened in Jan of 2021. I stuck with the classics - chicken cutlet and fried rice. It's a very classic Singapore western food taste profile. Not amazing, but not bad either. A bit salty for me, but I'm sure the general public should be ok.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: You can tell easily from the rude stall assistant auntie and unpalatable food. Moments of cooking so cack handed and unprofessional, that I want to congratulate the stall on its incompetence.

Followed Thomson East Coast Line MRT Train ads and found this restaurant.

For 5 pax we ordered
Lo Hei with Salmon
Crispy skin chicken
Yam Ring with scallops
Stir fried Vegi
Braised Pork with bun (Chinese hamburger)
Mango Pur√©e Sago

Overall experience: Priceless. Dishes all taste good.

The food there is really great, ambience is good too. I wasn't even intending to eat there but the smell was just so enticing. I was walking past and there this mouth-watering aroma. And I went to check it out, the variety there not bad, so I ordered the beef don. Although it was on the pricey side, they do deliver the goods. Beef was cooked just nice, not overcooked and chewy like many other restaurants, the texture was great. The sauce was amazing, when it arrived, there was a wonderful "grilled-smokiness" smell, wonderful. Rice was cooked right, not mushy, good job.  Would be happy to return again

The food is good. Very well organised for taking orders, serving by chefs and the clearing. The disadvantage for non Chinese is many of the waiters do not speak in English. Should add salted agg buns and hot drinks eg hot lemongrass
The food is quite good but the air is bad. My hair and clothes are smelly which stink me and my bag throughout the the time when I was there and when I am traveling back.

We went there on Deepavali.

It was our first visit.

And we enjoyed every one of the dishes we ordered.

If you're someone who appreciates homecooked foods, you should visit this restaurant and try out the food for yourself.

But if you're someone who enjoys alittle more of a sophisticated kind of ambience or even food styles (a.k.a atas/fine dining) then you may not enjoy dining at this place.

But for me and my family, we'll certainly come back and dine here again.

Thank you Grace's Pot Indian Restaurant!üòä
Dumplings and pancake was not too bad. The gyoza ü•ü is good. Do try the red bean pancake dessert which serve with good filling of good standard of tea beans paste.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Order food delivery for supper. One of the egg prate is half burnt.

Relocated from 51 Lorong 6 Toa Payoh.

Here you get to enjoy one of the most authentic western food.

Famous for its Sirloin Steak, this is the real deal!

Must try.

We only had a sambal chicken rice bowl and sambal fried tanghoon for lunch. Both were good enough for us to think of coming back with friends to try more dishes, especially the fish head curry. Will update!
No frills eatery with no aircon. Had fried mee sua, fried batang fish & garlic vegetable plus 2 drinks $27. Just nice for 2 persons

One of the best hotpots I've had! The set meals are perfect! Great variety of dishes, so delicious! The broth was amazing too. Can see myself coming back to this place. Value for money ‚ô•Ô∏è A gem of a find from Paradise Group
Great and tasty prata time with family and friends.
Tried the signature wagyu steak and it is quite dissapointed. Meat is a bit tough and need more seasoning. Rice is too much.
Good food, comfortable seating. All you can eat.
Consistent dim sum & Cantonese cuisine in the heartlands but portions have reduced over time, becoming more costly by the day!

Great value Japanese food. I always felt the bento set was one of the most value Japanese meals in Singapore.

I added on the squid from Hokkaido based on their recommendation and it was great too.

The place is always kept clean and tired so it is great especially for a season of covid19.
Love the heng hua style of food here. Especially the soft fried bee hoon. Food is serve fast.
food is nice. staff is friendly. outside seats too many mosquitoes.
Under rated Malay food stall. Long queue, fast serving. Good portion price ratio. Great tasting food with good variety. Nasi lemak must try, mee goreng when available.

Hits and misses here. Wait can be long during peak hours and they have a tendency to mess up are customised orders (even simple things like change of drinks). Clearing up the kfc cafe area will allow for more seating area. All these are made up for by the fantastic uncle who gives out sticky notes wishing students all the best for their study.
Very nice place to chill and drink! Do try out the coconut jelly it is awesome. Handmade by the owner!

Super nice green Nasi Lemak and very affordable! Even after adding additional ingredients beyond the "Standard Pack", it is still consider cheap vs other Nasi Lemak stall (Muslim and non Muslim). Great chicken wings. Be prepared for long Q if you come after 11.30pm.

Good service each time I come. The place is quieter in the afternoon but dinner is a like a screaming restaurant especially when you are seated near kids. The food is not consistent especially the salads. Sometimes you get nice vegetable ‚Ä¶

Had a bite here after a hike. It's beautifully nestled inside the Bishan-Ang Mo Kio Park so there's greenery all around. The entrance is very insta-worthy & the night view imo is nicer. Service was prompt & we got seated and ordered their ToriYard signature maki. We waited a good 20mins+ for it to be ready and it wasn't served cold. The rice was room-temperature & so were the ingredients. Pretty disappointing after a long wait. I would still give them another chance as we went on a public holiday & they were probably overwhelmed. Wanna try their Yakitori - it was serving up plate after plate at good speed unlike our maki üò¢
Great service and food. Portion is generous and tasty.

Came here because of Food King. We ordered Dong Po Pork Belly, fried fish with chrysanthemum sauce and the pumpkin prawn balls. They were all good, huge portions but not fantastic. With the family crowd on that Saturday we went, you know this zhi char has a certain standard that they won't fall below. But food-king good? Hmm probably not.

Came during the lunch rush hours‚Ä¶ the servers are very attentive to the customers‚Ä¶ ensuring that the waiting queue gets updated on the seating arrangements‚Ä¶ orders are taken prior to sitting to save time‚Ä¶ my favourite dish though was the pumpkin cake‚Ä¶ will have to come try the other dishes‚Ä¶

We've had a fantastic experience here twice now! We came for drinks and small bites one night, and had breakfast here on a separate occasion -- both were wonderful! Food quality was very high and service was attentive, but the absolute highlight was the quality of the cocktails! Very inspired Asian flavour combinations, one of the best bars we've been to in Singapore.
Tried their kway teow grg, lontong kering, nasi grg kampong, all so nice! My fav malay stall in jurong west so far! Highly recommended!

After all the hype, we tried this place out to avoid driving all the way to Jurong.

The food here is average at best. Jurong is better, at least from our last trip in Nov 2021.

The chendol is nothing like those in Penang or even any parts of Singapore. So it's bad. Skip it.

Charkoay teow was moist which is unlike Penang which is dryer.
