Prawn mee was the only bright spot followed by KL Hokkien mee.

Didn't try out other dishes... Not sure if I want to waste my stomach space again there.

Awesome place to dine 5 paxs for nowü§£ü§£for vaccinated only
Love the claypot rice, Assam laksa, meesiam, my girl like the minced pork porridge, meehoon kueh, chendol @$2 only.  Good that are using porcelain bowls which I felt is home.
Some masia noleh food is not nice, here is ok and the best one is jurong point.

Rabak bro. Must pay for tap water, soup of the day served in a tiny bowl. I ordered steak, the veggies they served with the steak were slightly burnt. Ordered medium rare steak, came almost well done. Ice cream for dessert was lousy also. Service also not that good.
Food was good. Service was efficient. Thumbs up to manager Andy, very nice and friendly. Amazing customer service, a role model for all staff to follow

Patronize this eatery very often. They serves authentic Thai Food at reasonable prices. I personally love their pineapple rice, chicken carshew rice, basil meat rice, etc...the list goes on. Try them and you know what I mean. Come earlier to avoid the dinner crowd.
Their healthier choice teriyaki chicken with brown rice is not bad ($9.90++). Golden wings, which came with a side of coleslaw was quite good too. Service could be abit more attentive and responsive.

The signature samshui chicken was succulent and as always, its standard was maintained. Tried a new dish, the Ah Po Ginger fried rice. The amount of ginger was just nice and the rice was fragrant. The claypot tofu deserves a try too.

Prices are low and portions are big.
Taste is decent but nothing to shout about. Soups were abit diluted, partner's mixian was cooked to mushiness, but mine was fine.
Ice jelly was a let-down, tasted just like regular jelly. Probably will not return.

Bare minimal decor, the place is hidden behind the bus stop at Novena Regency, is the only place with queue during dinner.

Known for their Jajangmyeon and Tangsuyuk (Korean version of sweet and sour pork). But unlike other places, their Tangsuyuk (from $24/small) is made of deep-fried pork stripes, lightly battered before being coated in a well-balanced sweet & sour sauce. Cut into bite-size, it is pretty addictive to munch on though it‚Äôs recommended to eat them hot as it hardens when it‚Äôs cool.

For those who prefer something spicy, Kkanpunggi aka Spicy Garlic Fried Chicken (from $32/small) can set your tongue on fire. Deliciously fried chicken, it is enrobed in a red spicy sauce filled with peppers and garlic

Best Chicken Chop I've ever had in Singapore! I paid $15 for a Chicken chop with a drink and a side under their lunch special on weekdays! I'll definitely come back here again. I recommend Collin's for those looking for a good western meal. I also loved the fast service and friendly staff.

The wait is worth it. The restaurant is small, yet they did everything they could to ensure the patrons are kept comfortable. I can see if this place is maxed out on capacity the air conditioner will not be sufficient. Take note it's a self-service restaurant so you need to take your cutleries and the curry sauce (choose between chicken and fish). Do note that you will need to request for particular order for vegetarians. The  Mini ultimate murtabak is to die for, it's crispy and with cheese and dice chicken... Hmmm. And Teh Halia is also very well created - I had 2 cups in one seating.
Lovely steak on offer and affordably price food.
Delicious and filling!

The worst decision I made today is to have lunch at Umi sushi Mount Alvernia.

Order a ramen and found a piece of plastic roughly 5cm long and 2mm wide inside the soup. Brought the item to counter and the staff gave me a ‚Äúnew bowl‚Äù, old noodle with new soup, probably boiled together as the previous one with the plastic in.

I am a breastfeeding mother and I am really worried that I may have ingested plastic (thus causing harm to the baby thru my produce) becos the plastic surely doesn‚Äôt look like a complete piece! Decided to stop breastfeeding my baby from now on, thanks to the excellence  service of Umi Sushi.

I noticed on Google review, that just two months ago another reviewer has encountered the same ‚Äúplastic incident ‚Äú at Mount Alvernia outlet! Well done management!

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Worst restaurant to order from waiting time 1hr plus

Hong Kong Street Family Restaurant at the corner at Novena Gardens (opposite Novena). We ordered 5 dishes for only 2 pax and ate them all. Very yummy and very suitable for weekend family dinners. Come early to avoid the queues. ‚Ä¢ Pork Ribs Butter Gourd ($10) // Har Cheong Gao ($10) // Cereal Prawn ($18) // Seafood Yi Mee ($6) // Sum Lor Hor Fun ($7) ‚Ä¢ Follow me on Instagram to swipe left for more yummy food! ‚Ä¢ #letsguide #burpple #foreverhungry #singaporeeats #instagood #chope #hungryeatwhat #hungryeatwhere #foodie #foodiesg #hungrygowhere #chope #entertainerapp #sgfood

(Translated by Google) Drink first

(Original)
Minum dulu

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: my family was being blessed by a sumptuous breakfast as the household members were down with covid. it was a really nice meal, especially the char siew puff that taste amazing!! the porridge comes with a lot of ingredients and it‚Äôs tasty. service is extremely good too. my friend mentioned that she asked for a change of item and called them up they were so nice to help. highly recommended!
Come here to eat buffet with bro and relative, price reasonable and service is fast although is al-carte buffet
Ordered the premium steak don and pork slices don. The meat portion is surprisingly sizeable for the price and seasoning is really good. Very value for money.

Very high quality food yet friendly on the wallet. We ordered the 4 pax meal and have no more space for the oysters. Will come back again to try the Japanese oysters. Happy hour rate at only $2 per oyster. Staff are very friendly and willing to accommodate. Kudos to Jeremy for the good hosting!

the quality of customer service is totally out ,food nice the almost like malaysia ,but the price and quantity in the portion  are very little i bought kuay teow goreng for 6.80$ the contain look alike 4.50$, arrogant staff quality of serving is out.
A restaurant with nice and tasty food. Price is reasonable and not crowded. Love the location and free parking!
the best Muslim stall in Toa Payoh.  Good Beef Rendang.  But, on the expensive side.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Delicious! A wide selection and affordable. Egg tarts and char siew sow are nice.  Siew mai har gow are delectable.. only the steamed pork ribs falls short a little.. affable cashier despite the long queue.. however the queue seems to be shorter than the fishball queue next to it.

Nice food
Very good dry fish curry
Affordable price
31 kelantan lane outlet. WORST western food ever. Portion was so small and dry.

Meat quality & taste of beef, chicken and pork is good. But their combi grill is extremely not value for money :( - makes u pay more for 3 small cuts of meat which I personally feel adds up to less meat than if u just order regular chicken/pork chop‚Ä¶
Sells cheesy popcorn chicken porridge, which was a fusion well-done

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Breakfast here, small hawker center but the Laksa sooo good and perfect match with calamansi juice üòçüòç the price also cheap. Stall in the middle dont know the name bcos thats chinese character

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Just normal Malay food, nothing great..excuse me!! This is not padang food ok. If you guys state this as nasi Padang then something is wrong with your taste buds.some dishes lack of spice.
This eatery is just good to fill up your tummy.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Well, it's a mixed rating. Food was good and super cheap!!! 6 of us full grown adults, all the meat and seafood etc it only cost us $118.80!! Amazing! I think cheaper than supermarket and cooking at home!! I downside, this branch has no Aircon. Some people like it but i do prefer if they have AC and a super strong suction ventilator. Overall happy.. HAPPY CAMPER!

I visited in lunch time. They don't serve ta doori meals then. I ordered Curry chicken briyani set, Butter chicken prata set and cheese prata. Butter chicken curry had aroma of charcoal roasted. Other curry sauces were all different taste. All of them  were yummy.
I would try tandoori meals at dinner time.

Review for : Take away for dinner. +  weekday dim sum buffet.

Dimsum buffet: Book and start the buffet at 3pm. As with everyone else, you'll be given an appetiser and pot of tea before the ala carte dishes is served in push carts. Going when it first starts ensures that you get a portion of all the dishes available as the service progresses. The dishes are served in good timing and don't rush to have multiple servings of each dish, unless u really want to, as there's new dishes constantly up until the 1hr20mins-ish mark where desserts start. Some dishes were a hit, (custard bun, red bean banana roll, char siew bao, siew mai, fish skin) some were mediocre (lotus glutinous rice, century egg porridge, egg tart). But otherwise, it's good value. Definitely worth it, had 20ish dishes between the 2 of us. We were super stuffed just an hr in.

Take away dinner: the lady taking our order was frank with regards to what dishes were good to order as take away. Generally, the food was decent, the duck was flavorful and tender. Radish fried kway teow was flavourful, altho the small portion was half size that of the small portion of the eefu. The sesame pork was a little disappointing, as it was just roasted sesame salad sauce with pork, not unique or memorable, can pass. * Note: takeaway orders have 20% off for almost all dishes. Offer not valid for delivery or dine in. Validity till unknown.

food tasted very average, definitely had better. super pricey and the portions were really small as well. the only good dishes were the xiao long bao and the la zhi ji but the rest were average
service was decent but didn‚Äôt feel like the meal was very worth it

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The staff are friendly and helpful. Overall experience was good.
The food is not too bad but pretty disappointed that they changed their garden salad (unlike the ones they show in their menu) to typical coleslaw..

Great food. The sashimi is very value for money as the cuts are very thick. Tempura is crispy, yums.

The place is right beside Sheng Shiong. It has an old school charm to it.

The place was packed on a Saturday night, had to wait 45 mins for our food when we placed order at 7.15pm. Come earlier if you have kids in the group.

They had bookshelves full of comics, but it‚Äôs all in Japanese language üòÖ
Food is tasty and not too oily. Price is reasonable.
Good price point! Food is yummy. Love the mushroom sauce and minestrone soup is tasty! Recommend the soursop drink. Lunch set is available.
Very nice

Abit on the pricey side for a prata but the quality is undoubtedly one of the best that I've tasted. The curries are excellent and I would highly recommend the mutton curry, tender and yum üòã tasty. I would go again when I want to pay that kind of price again for a great prata. üëç

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
The quality of the dim sum is so so
Rude stall assistant gives it a negative impression. Porridge taste very plain. The rest of the dimsum taste is very heavy on the gravy. The only upside is that they have many varieties. Price wise is not worth it.
Decent home cooked style Malay meals at affordable prices.  It was fragrant and the dishes didn't taste complicated at all even though they were.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Missed the traditional old taste although it is getting pricey. Service is getting worse. Arrived at 7.30pm, wanted to order chicken drumstick but was told unable to do so unless I order half chicken. Curry fish head is too salty as well. Sambal kangkong is at $9.10 for a very small plate. Hope to see better service and improve taste in the future.

The Famous Kitchen!
Maybe due to covid issue, not much ppl dine in. Food here was nice. I had choose the KL Da lu mee, assam fish and dessert is the O n√©e (sweet yam paste).
DA lu mee got enough wok hey, taste exactly like what I have tasted in KL.
Assam fish not so sour as what I like. Fish is fresh also.
Not to be said, till now I still miss the yam paste.
Those who see this post should go and have a try.
Nice bento
Tasty food. Reasonable prices. Decor is pretty plain but compensated by the quality of the food
Tasty and affordable priced Thai food. The portions are generous too.

At this point, it is unfortunate that Ichiban is synonymous for awful service.

We have spoken to the manager after our meal and they were very understanding but this was what happened:

Walking to my seat, a guy pushing a trolly (with trash and a bin if i may highlight) came out from the kitchen and blocked the path so i went back and stood at the side so he could pass. I watched as he rudely used his hand to gesture to someone to move out of his way.

After speaking to the manager, it seems like that guy was the dishwasher and he was rude to the staffs too.

Introduced by a Malaysian bestie and claimed as the authentic Malaysian taste üòÇüòÇ
The Curry Pig Skin Chee Cheong Fun is recommended.

Should try the Dry Mee with Char Siew too, the sauce used is different from most of culinaries here.

Be prepared that it is crowded on weekend morning, decided to go for takeaway on 2nd visit.
Good taste with reasonable price

We had Katsu chicken truffle sando and Australian Wagyu sando and they were both amazing!! Their matcha panna cotta was good too. Their service was beyond excellent!! Thank you Zamzi, Iries and Nareeth!
Prawn was great. ribs were so-so. noodles were OK.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
Prawn Mee with Clams ($6.50). Was surprised that a halal prawn mee could still be good even though no pork was used in the broth. Lots of chicken bones were used instead of pork bone, together with anchovies, dried shrimps and prawn shells.

Those who like their prawn noodles dry should also like that the noodles were savoury and fragrant with lots of fried shallots in the mix.
Good food, order pork chop fried rice and the chicken soup

Extremely poor service. Ordered take out during non peak season and was made to wait 45 mins. ( I was told the wait would be 10-15 mins). The worse was the food was just sitting at the counter and left cold, and none of the service staff bothered to call out for me. If I did not check with the counter I would have been waiting for eternity. To make this unpleasant experience even worse, the service staff still came up with excuses to justify for not calling out for the numbers. Ridiculous...

Great concept with very unique proposition of food with price.
Lot of vegetarian options available which most of the other places are missing .
For sure let‚Äôs others know and visit again

Ok Can TRY!!The service was IMPECCABLE! Had a GREAT time and to top it off the FOOD was GREAT!! DESPITE BEING OPPOSITE Michelin- starred Tsuta, this place could stand tall and proud on its own merit!!
Ordered from Deliveroo in July: small portions for poke bowl, not filling -> highly overpriced.
Taste no bad and price is reasonable
Jjm is decent, but not the best, however, their sweet and sour pork surprised me, highly recommended..99/100! Simply can't stop ü§©üëç
Food is good, very fresh. Hope the quality will stay. Like the style to order at counter and collection when buzzed.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Great place for Thai mookata (bbq). Inexpensive and meat are well marinated. If local Thais choose to satisfy their mookata craving here rather than golden mile, you can be assured of the quality. Just be warned that long queues are expected on Fridays and weekends.
Sushi was passable at best. Fairprice sushi is better honestly.. Soba and tempura wasn't fantastic either. Definitely NOT worth the premium

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
20/09/2020  - Ordered via Grabfood on 19/09/2020, 1pm++ (Tampines).  These are what I received (1st 3 images), all overnight food.

21/09/2020 - Owner left mobile number for me to contact him and send me a replacement with extra chicken wings on the same day I contact him (last image). There is great different in the items. And those in the last image should be their normal standard (but not Tampines Branch).
Okay . Because I stay above this coffeeshop.

Taste wise is fine for me. Choose fried beancurd,prawn fitters and 2 others. Minimum 4 pieces, cost $7.59. Can use PayNow or cash payment, do not accept Paywave or credit card. Located at B2 near Kopitiam foodcourt

Located at Blk 711 . The food is normal however hard to find such food in hawker now. The owner or the the worker is just too rude. Luckily that the business is still running  with that kind of attitude around
Mix Grill. A coffeeshop style western food stall that is almost the anchor stall of the whole coffeeshop, their cuts are decent and you feel like you get the bang of your buck.

Have tried Set D - Sweet & Sour Pork + Stir fried Seafood Black Bean Sauce Noodles (Jajangmyeon), the food portion is big and should be enough for 3 persons with normal appetite. Authentic Korean food as the restaurant is opened by Korean, especially the Jajanhmyeon is a must try. The food is a bit pricey and the variety is not much, topokki is not available too.
Good food, friendly staff, service also good

Very good rice and beef, very well cooked. No vegetables, which would make the meal healthier. Japanese style, with a nice location, enough space to avoid to be too close to other people. Good place to have a quick and tasty dinner. The machines to order are a little bit counter-intuitive, being connected exclusively with their related local stands.

Do not visit this shop. Very poor service, did not inform about waiting time for order. Ended up waiting for an hour since refund for order was rejected. Got partial refund for order in the end. Food was not so great as well.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Theva portrayed a very good service. Went the extra mile to assist us. Good job knowledge and very friendly.
Good quality is quite good .. service is good too .. was there in the VIP room and service is really good and attentive too .. will patronise again

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Convenient place near junction 9 to satisfy my prata cravings. Air conditioned interior augmented with fans made the meal there quite tolerable. Although enclosing the area meant the floor/table tops sometimes were greasy when the cooking got busy.

Had roti prata and teh tarik here. Both were of normal quality. Fish curry that came with it was good!
Tom yam fried rice superüëçn other's menu too

Was initially reluctant to try this place given the many unfavourable reviews, but am so glad I gave it a shot.

The quality of the food considering the price point was excellent, way better than expected and definitely a mark above the sister restaurant ichiban sushi, also in amk hub. Loved the fried salmon skin (soo crisp) and potato salad (daughter claims its the best version ever). Miso soup was too salty for me though.

The robot "waiter" and cute trains will appeal to kids. The digital queue system was so convenient as well - you'll be prompted via text when your table is ready, so you can run your errands in the meantime.

Staff were sincere and customer centric. Well done!

Ordered the glass noodle prawns and squid in lime broth. Both are so good! The price is a bit steep for the noodle prawns, as there are only 3 prawns of medium size but the portion is a lot. The squid broth is amazing and is one of their signature dishes.
Good and affordable

The quality of cooking is consistent, texture of home made noodles, fish balls and fish cake is excellent!  Increased in price: small bowl at $4.50 and large bowl at $5.50. Mostly 2 of us order the large.
Value for money.
Expect to queue for 10-20 mins on average between 9am to 10.30am

All time favourite for Penang prawn noodle and Lor mee since my 1990s.. the lady boss has retired and pass the baton to the son. Although taste diff a little but still good, especially the specially homemade dry prawn, fantastic, you can‚Äôt find it elsewhere.
The only thing is the noodle price has been increased over time and time, not so affordable to fill an empty stomach.
But no choice if you have a craving.
Inflation and rent cost is real.

Love their dumpling, it is a must have üòç

Steam, and fried dumpling is good ‚Ä¶
Great non greasy Filipino food!

Have to agree with some of the reviewers here. The cleaners slam the utensils and talk way too loudly. The fried kway teow staff has attitude. I stood in front and the fella just ignored.

So I left and ordered the claypot rice. The young man disappeared for the longest time before he gave us our change. We then indicated we would like to purchase the drinks that came with the meal. The fella directed us to another store some distance away. And never gave us receipts. So we hard to make a second trip because the drinks stall asked for proof of paurchase.

First and last time at this lousy place.

Not happy to work, then don't. Customers are not responsible for your perceived lot in life.

Found this place on Google map. The broth of the prawn noodle is good ( a little sweeter compare to SG prawn noodle ).
But I like it very much. I will be coming back.

Order came wrongly and it took more than 20 mins for my first place of sashimi to come.

The outlet still has tons of empty seats which obviously show that it's not busy at all. Things were pretty much self service. My orders only came after I informed the staff that my orders have not arrive yet.

This outlet at Jurong point have way lesser people compared to other outlets even though it's a weekend. I can see the reason now.

went during a Monday rainy evening as trying to avoid the crowds. food is good.  service is fine . was lucky as they were having half price promotion on combo grill . two adult with three children.  enjoyed. bill is about 90 dollar.  without promo should be around 130
Had a yusheng here. It was ok just that it was a bit too dry (not enough sauces). Salted egg fish skin is crispy and tasty. Marmite pork ribs are tender. Tofu with golden mushrooms are nice too!

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Mookata stall with many variety of food.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Food is tasty and the ambience is good too , but need to improve in service side

During one of my visit I experienced these

The waiter didn't took my Order Properly, and the other staffs are also not so professional in taking orders and serving them

One of our dish got delayed so much and at last we cancelled that order and left

Need to improve in their Service side

Food is worthy , some mouth watering dishes are available , Got many Vegetarian options.

May be this day isn't the best day for me and the Restaurant

Authentic Indian food. Very attentive owner who recommended us a dish. But was a little insistent on us not taking a spicy one. I don't know if it is good or bad ü§£.
Their food is Amazing, flavours of spice is abundance. Cheese nan might be better to use shredded cheese instead of slice cheese. Makes not so evenly spreaded.

Overall: still an amazing place for Indian food.

This is considered out of the way although a short walk from the MRT station. Luckily we decided on a late night dinner instead reaching at 9:30pm on a Fri night. Even then we can still see the remnants of the dinner crowd so would advice those who want to eat in peace and not wait too long to go before or after the peak hours.

We only ordered 3 dishes and all 3 feels quite solid. The drunken chicken soup was tasty and full of Chinese herbs. Both my dad and mum can make better soups but this is as good as it gets when you are eating out.

We had the egg omelette whilst pretty normal for tze char was done pretty well. The egg was not rubbery, and one can get a good bite from the other ingredients egged into it.

The pumpkin sauced prawns were the highlight we think of the dinner. One may be lulled into thinking this is a healthier version of salted-egg yolk sauces. I rather think this is a deconstruction of what is common place with something else surprising. The creamy feel of the sauce when one bites into the prawns is eyebrow lifting to say the least. And I can't help but wonder what is added to replicate the salted egg yolk but not kinda taste.

Overall is definitely a place worth checking out, if you have the time and patience to travel all the way (remember how crappy the red line is right now). The food will reward you for your trouble.

Though on 2nd thought, there is always this naggy feeling that the tze char store is as good as the chef is. And no chef and his team is permanent. If anything, I would savor the experience until the next discovery.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: It took me 1 hour for me to get my order ready. Other customer already got their food, but not me. When i try to ask about my order, one of the staff with specs talk to me rudely saying "ya ya ya, we still cooking." To be honest, this used to be one of my favourite restaurant before they change to a new name.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Nice place and nice ambience. We went pretty late at night, was quiet and service was fast. They place is quite honest too as they were clearing the food that was leftover since earlier in the day and did not serve for dining (i.e. the mutton sambal, chicken sambal etc.).

The staff are friendly and even at late night they go beyond the extra mile to ensure you are comfortable.

Very nice ambience and nice food. Staff very polite and helpful - eg. Benyathip

Will come again.
Reasonable price for food here.. great experience

Average. Cha Shu is on the lacking side, pretty tough to chew. The rest are ok, not exactly cheap and affordable factoring quality. Compare to many local raman F&B which are just selling slightly more expensive but taste way better.

Soup lacks depth and Cha Shu was tasteless.
Gyozas was not bad.
Won‚Äôt be back again

Default Order: Burrito Bowl (different variants)
Times ordered ready: 40+
Food Quality: Great
Timeliness: Excellent, never delayed
Taste: Excellent

Recommendation: Spicy Chicken Burrito Bowl with additional pico de gallo
Cheap and tasty!
Friendly staff, great dining experience with a range of delicious dishes.
Located at B2 of AMK Hub, this foodcourt is a very crowded outlet. The food is nice and the price is quite reasonable.

The auntie over there super rude. dk she pms or what. We Said pay by paynow. Then she go press paylah. OK, my paylah no money so need to do transaction. and then she chasing for payment non-stop impatiently. She forgot to issue the Number tag for the food and still raise her voice.
Ok

Cozy cafe for dinner, served mostly western food. Teriyaki chicken pizza was surprisingly yummy and crispy! Loaded with sauce and mayo. The pan seared barramundi was fresh, paired with mashed potatoes and salad. Kids Mac and cheese was a small portion and comes with a drink. Service was excellent and attentive. The lights was dim yet warm. It was crowded for a Thursday night! Overall, the food is good, will come back for waffles and ice cream next time!
Honestly speaking nothing to shout about! For the price point you can get better Korean food out there! For e.g obbjang or SBCD. Can come if there‚Äôs  no queue

Good and reasonable priced Halal authentic Japanese food.

Ramen and Udon were well worth the price. Kids love the Udon.

Ordered the Royal Rumble set which include a piece of everything.
The highlight is the chilli, not too sweet and not too overpowering, it is just nice for my liking .

Highly recommended if you are craving for a fantastic nasi lemak!

It was not crowded when I went. The grilled chicken was nice. Rosti was crispy on the outside. Brownie with vanilla ice cream was good too. Attentive staff, appreciate
Ms/Mrs. Jia Xuan.

Food is fine. One staff was very rude and mocked my accent to other employees as I was ordering. I guess she thought I couldn‚Äôt hear her. If the owner of this restaurant sees this, pls get to the bottom of who this is (appeared to me a manager as she was holding paper, female, in her 20s?). Looks like some re-training and disciplinary action are needed. Very bad experience.
Old school nasi lemak and great value! Not to be missed if you visiting Lor 7 Toa Payoh, do come early.

Excellent restraunt.üòäWe can get North Indian food here. Such as chicken tikka, biriyani rice , prata and others .Their chikken tikka taste really awesome. I personally recommend it. If you loves North Indian food can go for this without any doubt .Excellent and authentic north Indian food.Lunch time will be crowded. Most reasonably priced. Staff and Manager Naveed are more than willing to go the extra mile for customer satisfaction.Great teamwork also .

Underrated stall, they deserve more stars. The pork loin was great, both my kids love it. The portion was juz nice for small eaters like my family. Steak was nicely grilled, char grilled chicken is still tender and juicy. Not forgetting to mention I had to walk a distance home and food still taste excellent. Don't take my words, go try it and review yourself.

Very nice and chill ambience, tasty food (must try the mutton satti soru - claypot rice) and affordable drinks (their Guinness on tap is refreshingly good). Definitely recommend to head down with family and friends!
Delicious authentic thai foods by native thai chef. The price is inexpensive and service is good.

Yishun safra feels pretty new and clean. Food was served hot and really good. Pricey for prata, but the creative menu is definitely worth trying out. Looking forward to try their next limited time special menu item.

the diy bowls are pretty decent for the ingredients. but i ordered the truffle fries and the fries tasted very weird - its the taste of the overused cooking oil. granted it is during peak lunch hour, i still don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs fair to the consumers
Super nice beef rendang... juicy and the spice  level is great

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: On a second floor of a wet market... The food section is divided into 4 parts with lot of local good "recommend" foods... Nostalgic feeling to an old town... But just don't go during night time, almost all are closed...
The roast duck was AWESOME! That's probably the most important information you need to know

Food quality is consistently good. Home style cooking and festive food, all available. Good for daily meals and family celebrations.

Parking at the IRAS building next door is plentiful. I have changed to parking in their basement due to all the roadworks. Drive slowly and Look carefully for Novena Gardens entrance to car park. Easy to miss.
First visit and impressed by the the hygiene and homely taste,  would visit often .

1. First the concept is attractive and interesting.
2. However, the udon is too salty and got light soya bean sauce smell overpowering.
3. The fish got fishy smell
4. The cutting of the fish not properly cut as can eat some part of the fish that is hard.
5. The table is already so small and service provider can‚Äôt even cleared the table proactively
Quiet place, not crowded during weekday lunches, good for catch up
Excellent food and affordable. Nice ambience and easy to talk service is great

Great food - tried out most of these dishes for the first time and we loved the taste of spices. The curries were well flavored and spiced. The grilled pineapples were something we haven tried before and it was good although we had to wait 20 mins for it. The boneless mutton curry was well flavour but part of the meat were pretty tough to chew on - it would have been 5 stars if the meat had been more tender. The chicken dum briyana was good and infused with the aroma of spices.  Overall, a positive dining experience.

My only option for good Prata in Yishun, the quality mostly matches that of the outlet in Springleaf Road. The waiting is longer though, probably due to the smaller kitchen and staff size. Safra members get a small discount as well.
The Long Tong is my favourite food here. For $3.50, it is value for money. Lotsa veggie and the gravy is tasty. And don't forget the sambal, it is a must!

Visited the Phoenix Indian Restaurant during Kids Stop visit. Tried only Vegetarian food. All items were tasty and delicious. Were served well on time.  The restaurant service is very good. Staff are extremely courteous. Haven't seen a better North Indian Restaurant (tasty and economical at the same time) in this part of the city. Would surely visit again. Highly recommended for good North Indian food!
Affordable and tasty food, one of the cheapest Sapporo beers in town. Friendly and warm staff. Definitely a surprise to find this gem in the heart of Tai Seng.

Definitely the cheapest in the Bishan-AMK area. Quantity was adequate. Taste was above average.
The lady from the stall is pleasant and friendly.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
A casual, friendly and cosy place for Thai steamboat aka Mookata. It gives a true blue heartlander experience within a coffee shop yet keeping up with the trends. Very affordable at $22 nett for a set for 2 pax excluding drinks. Ala carte option available.

Love the al fresco ambience even when it's bustling with people enjoying the food with family and friends. A perfect get-together spot.

Mookata is essentially a hot plate BBQ plus a ring of boiling chicken soup stock around it so you get to enjoy the best of both worlds. Grill your meat with the pork fat given, and boil your vegetables in the tasty soup that has no MSG. Then, dip your grilled meat into their homemade spicy chilli-and-garlic sauce. Heavenly! I could eat this all night.

If you need more food, simply add on other dishes at only $1.90 to $2.40 nett. The boss goes around chatting with patrons, and he does seem like he loves what he is doing.

Icing on the cake would be the quality draft German beers the coffee shop owner sells right beside. It complements the mookata perfectly.

Will definitely be back!

Mala hotpot with beef. Soup mild spiciness, beef added flavour to the soup. Homemade tofu thumb up, with a little minced pork and spring onion soya sauce blends well. La Zi Ji, bits of chicken skin, was crispy. Also their Mongolian salted egg pork another must try(not in pic)
Fun concept for a gathering. Cook & eat together. Best thing is fuss free after cook, you don't need to clean up the mess. Haha!

Fresh and good crabs. Order the Sri Lankan crab if you go to avoid disappointment in case if full house booking.
We had chilli crab, pepper crab and butter crab. Crab meat was thick and yummy. The butter crab had crispy crumbs which were really good.  The chilli crab sauce was so delicious and the mantou to dip in...yum yum
Book in advance as restaurant could be full like our visit tonight.

love their steamed chicken, highly recommend 1/2 chicken for 2-3pax, with their chicken rice of course. the rice is a must-try, it goes wonderfully with their smooth, tender steamed chicken. also suggest their 3 egg spinach (ËããËèú) and thai style tofu. worth the money, i'm a frequent diner here for sure.

(Translated by Google) The grilled fish is crispy enough, the portion is big enough, the taste is good, and the price is reasonable

(Original)

Good food and service

One of the oldest hakka restaurant in Singapore. Bamboo windows, hazardous power sockets with too many plug-ins, round table with my grandmother's tablecloth, newspaper cutout on a piece of cupboard for a menu, and 1970s kampung photos made up the interior. Food looked homecooked, but the flavours are just....wow. Saucy salted chicken that fall off the bones paired with scallion oil dip, an unseemingly normal tofu with meat that exploded with umani, and a wok-hei fried-egg noodles are just some of the highlights. Love the vibes, would love to see this place stay like this.

Edit: Sitting by the windows, i saw the waiter rushing out with a bag of food towards a waiting car with windows rolled down. So they still do food pickup like the old days! Just so much memories!
cancelled our online order right before it had to be delivered :)? what the hell
food was goodÔºåfast and cheap

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: First time visited this restaurant. Affordable price and spacious. Fast service and good for enjoying good time with friends.
For lack of economical choice, this place fits the bill. Food is OK but not superb.

First visit, Vegetable Thali - It was excellent.
Egg fry was wonderful.

2nd Visit, Vegetable Biryani - Not to my taste and not like a usual Indian vegetable biryani.
Vegetable biryani should have vegetables (Flavoured rice or masala rice can't be named as Vegetable Biryani).

3rd Visit, Vegetable Biryani - Still the same but this time the side dish (Cauliflower 65 was mixed completely in dry so called Biryani Rice). This was not good compared to my 2nd visit.

Advice to customer is that know what you are ordering. No harm to ask people there about what you would get.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Today is the second eating yummy
The salad is very bad taste and only two kind of vegetables inside, and the price is $4.50, not valuable.

Aglio Olio was spicy and superb!
Root Beer Float came with a generous scoop of vanilla ice cream, bigger than A&W.

Could‚Äôve improved on the physical menu for better first impressions (it was an aged and flimsy laminated sheet)

Used entertainer 1 for 1 here (bento only). We added the sets where $10.90 more gets you some salad, one sushi, one scoop of ice cream, chawanmushi, half pint of Asahi draft (lager/dark). We shared the items in the 2 bento and I enjoyed the salmon the most. With entertainer, full marks. Very value for money
Notbad

First time to the restaurant and we had a great time.
We had top notch service from Ash & Fir. They were friendly and efficient.
The food was delicious & big in portion. All were served within minutes.
Dessert was absolutely delicious.
We had complimentary chicken wings & cake. It was very generous of the restaurant.
Will definitely come back

The failure of including the longevity birthday bun (of great significance) for order of their celebration set. C'mon, how many of a 70s does a person have? Your terrible act has spoilt a birthday celebration!  A promised return call to be made by their supervisor took hours (claimed that they were very busy when I am told that the call will be made within the next hour) and it was near their wind down operation hours by then.   A slipshod reply "we might have gotten too busy and we have forgot to pack in the longevity bun. We offer free desert at your next visit" - is that your method of service recovery? Do you even see the point that you have ruined a celebration by missing out on the most important item?!  And the food was way too salty!

I was pleasantly surprised by how good the food was, given that the store front looked rather assuming and there wasn't a snaking queue.

We ordered the set meal for 2 as we didn't want the hassle of deciding which dishes to order. The set meal came with 2 large bowls of rice, chicken, crab/fish (can't remember which) cakes and Tom yum soup. The portions were generous and is suited for a dining party of 3.

I loved the tom yum soup went very well with the rice and there was so much flavour. There were squid, fish and vegetables in the soup. The crab/fish cakes were not too oily and they went very well with the dipping sauces provided.

All in all, the meal was value for money and we'd definitely return again if we are in the area.
Good food üòä
Overall, a decent prata place.  Not too crowded, good to meet friends for prata and chat.

The char shao was lean so it is suitable for older folks but it certainly didn't look like what the pics in sign board.  When my duck and Chartham rice  order was taken I was asked if I  wanted to add an egg or anything else so I added bean sprouts but I didn't expect a whole plate of beansprouts to be served so damage was $13.30.Would be better if staff could inform me. Beansprouts were quite crunchy but a little salty for my liking. The place is loud and the staff voices were very loud.  Not my first place to have a nice quiet meal especially when food is jsut avg
A place where you can get many of Malaysia‚Äôs delicacies! And of which are up to standard and expectation. Would recommend Chendol and the pork cutlet curry rice. Asam laksa is not bad too!

UNO BEEF HOUSE is located in Toa Payoh along Lorong 5 Toa Payoh, at a coffeeshop under a HDB. Carpark is just beside the coffeeshop.

Beef Spaghetti ($6.00)
It was a spaghetti that was full of unpleasant surprises. The spaghetti tasted too soggy while the tomato sauce did not stand out. The real surprise was the mined beef as they felt like normal bolognaise. The beef was not unpleasant tasting but was just not outstanding from recommendation. Just a plate of tomato based sauce pasta with a touch of minced beef.

Mixed Platter ($12.00)
I went for the Mixed Platter which includes chicken chop, pork chop, bacon, ham, egg, fries, baked beans and a garlic bread. The pork chop was the only disappointment as the meat was dry, tough and was not well seasoned. On the other hand, the bacon was very flavorful and was crispy with a slightly charred side. The sunny side up egg had a really runny yolk which we gladly mopped up with the crispy garlic bread.

Bacon & Egg ($5.50)
Another friend went for the bacon as he could not resist, when the point was for him to try the pasta. Bacon was rather salt to have too many in my honest opinion but it was to his liking. It comes with two eggs, baked beans, garlic bread, coleslaw & fries. Nothing really fanciful about the dish. Probably something that would shine better for breakfast rather than lunch/dinner for the usual patrons.

Clad in the striking palette of black, gold and yellow by acclaimed British designer Anouska Hempel, this is one restaurant designed with Instagram in mind.

Helmed by Executive Chef Sebastian Goh who uses only healthy ingredients with no MSG. Our favourite dishes include the braised eggplant, roasted duck and the XO fried rice. Each dish is priced approximately $40, so a meal is roughly $80 per person without drinks.

Marriott Bonvoy members get dining discounts and points.
Don't understand the hype at all. Food was average. In fact it was way below average. The other 4 or 5 stars reviews are probably paid reviews to deceive the public. Avoid at all cost.
Great fried rice!!!!! I like

Famous for their fish bee hoon, however felt I hv tasted better. Generous portion of veggies and soup, but not the bee hoon and slice fish. For big eater, you may have to order two ‚ÄúL‚Äù portions as they only offer ‚ÄúS‚Äù and ‚ÄúL‚Äù. The rest of their stir fries are generally tasty and reasonable, which pretty much can get it anywhere in Singapore.
The bao is small but cost the same as big bao, very expensive. Not recommended.

Newly opened Little hidden gem here. Owners are very kind and humble and funny person. Mashed potato and coleslaw is a superb, fresh and own hand cut daily. Salmon is crispy at the skin but soft and juicy in the inner part. You can still feel the juice bursting in your mouth. The only wasted is the gravy, they put it on part of my favourite crispy salmon skin. The pork chop is very soft and tender, not oily and the portion is huge at only $8.90. But the homemade pepper sauce, I really wish I can take away only the gravy. I can already smell it once I collected. My eyes turned very big when I smelled. The fragrant is really addictive. Can feel they put a lot of effort in making it! Gonna try other dishes !
The guys at the stall at absolute Chads. Awesome food for a good price. Every other western stall in the area is average compared to this. Astons eat your heart out üíØ

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Very tasty and value for money portion. The soup is different daily too, not to mention it's free. Near closing, the soup ingredients will also be in so you will get more vegetables as well. Anyway, this is during the revamped launch and this is at the promo price of $1. After the promo period, they have a daily deal for chicken noodle and wanton mee, from 8am - 11am for just $2.50. Really nice

Patronised the kuantan nasi lemak at the northpoint outlet. Staffs are rude and lack training. In particular, there's this grumpy middle aged man, kept reprimanding his staffs for every single matter. Literally shouting away at customers who ordered lontong that there will be waiting time for ordering that. Though customers said ok, the staffs would still repeatedly shout that it require waiting time to order lontong. I ordered the nasi lemak takeaway, instead of handing over the food to me like any usual F&B staff would, he appear to be throwing the entire packet of food in plastic to me. The nasi lemak tasted average, if you need a benchmark, it's lower standard compared to Crave. I'm taking my money elsewhere for future lunch.

The best dish that I had was the hot and spicy soup, which was delicious.

The dumplings were not nice at all, as they had almost zero soup left in them, ‚Ä¶

The mash potato is to-die-for.

The Salmon is fresh and the hollandaise sauce compliments it perfectly!

The restaurant is far from town , but food wise is good. So no complain on that . If you had tried Putien‚Äôs restaurant food. This is similar but way cheaper. Portion we ordered for two person in small size but three dishes were way enough for us both. Price include two steam rice and added an extra rice $31. Recommended for family and friends . But this place is hot.
Staff is nice and friendly! Food comes extremely fast as well even during peak timings. Ordered bomb prata and tissue, gotta say its such a guilty pleasure

The shanghainese drunken chicken & black fungus in vinaigrette are decent. The xiao long bao & prawn dumpling are disappointing. Meat too tough, skin too thick. Prawn dumpling tasteless. Don‚Äôt be fooled by the drink ‚Äúgreen bean smoothie‚Äù. It‚Äôs not smoothie. Just crushed ice in green bean water. V thirsty after eating. Overall, will not recommend.
Googled ramen shops and decided to go this ramen shop. I had Hokkaido butter ramen set. This set comes with Gyoza and Watermelon. Gyoza was not so nice but the ramen was enough to satisfy me.

Paid $5 for a bowl of soya sauce chicken noodle, portion that came was small for the price paid, prob equivalent to $3.50 at other shops. Noodles was alright, done right qq and springy. Sauce is ok, abit saltish but taste better when dilute with soup. Soup quite tasteless, balances out salty sauce. Chicken breast was soft and tender. Slightly dry but tasty

Other reviews say it all. Will not visit again

Value for money 1/5
Taste 3/5

Honestly not bad if you're just coming for sushi and some other things if you aren't super hungry. It's obviously pricey compared to other foods but it's sushi and the quality of fish was okay. Salmon and salmon belly were the best quality out of what they had. Much better than sushi-go Jurong Point if you're coming for sushi. However the cooked foods here at genki was pretty lame and sushi go is probably better for that.

The floor manager look like you own him money. He would do his own things and let customer wait at the counter waiting to be seated even though there is empty space. He could have let customer sit down 1st and look at the menu 1st. The cashier counter also look messy and look very unpleasant for a restaurant. The place filled up with oil smell and your body will have the oil smell when you leave the place.

My first and last. The food not tasty at all. Unagi Don I ate are most terrible ever. I knew Unagi is full of bone, but this :( My cousin order the Sapporo Miso Ramen but the soup not like Miso is taste like butter soup.

It was a vegetarian restaurant. We ordered grilled spicy fish and the taste was okay but to me abit spicy. It will be very good for someone who prefer vegetarian foods as the quality no doubt is very good. I am more of a meat eater üòä
The portion is huge!! Signature noodle is not bad. Didn‚Äôt get to try others. Interior deco is interesting. Service is good.

So, Indian Muslim (Thai) food. Prata, Dosa, mutton, fried chicken, fried rice, fried noodles. The quality of the food, especially the prata varies with the cooks. Can be anything from above to below average. 24 hrs, so rather convenient. Don't expect good service through. And the cooks are always smoking behind the kitchen in the alleyway.
Good worthy food. Great taste and excellent service.  Keep it up!
Very good!

Founded in 1975 by Oh Joo Chong as a catering business, Gim Tim Restaurant opened its flagship outlet in 1989 in 157 Ang Mo Kio Avenue 4, where it remains to this day.
.
For over 33 years, Gim Tim Restaurant has positioned itself as a Modern Chinese mid-range dining experience, and it still draws in the crowds especially on weekends. Reservations therefore, are a must.
.
Ambience at Gim Tim Restaurant is modern classy, with a touch of sophistication. The air-conditioned interior is flanked by glass windows offering a view of the quiet estate, while warm lighting casts a soft glow over the white clothed tables and cushioned high back chairs.
.
A small chandelier gleams at the ceiling entrance, lending an air of elegant luxury. The exterior al-fresco seating is sheltered and just as comfortable, with a serving table at center stage.
.
Service at Gim Tim Restaurant is affable and attentive. The mature staff engage guests in jovial lighthearted banter, yet work efficiently at taking orders, fulfilling requests, and clean up quickly when diners leave.
.
Sometimes, they proactively ask to clear finished plates and top up drinks. Staff demonstrate good product knowledge and offer astute recommendations.
.
Food at Gim Tim Restaurant is Modern Chinese cuisine, centered around Hokkien, Cantonese, and Teochew cuisines. Chef Lai Yong Meng draws on the best techniques honed over the years, and with fresh premium ingredients, each dish is a delight.
.
Popular award-winning favourites and unique signature house creations feature on their extensive menu. Portions are sized for communal group sharing. Prices are mid-range for a restaurant, budget about SGD $62 per person.
great food and ambience though it is a food court. all kinds of beer could be found there  only thing is the time it closes 10 pm .zichar is good
Food is good and place is clean, staff very good and attentive. Food price on high side but its worth paying. Easy parking just opp thr shop. Keep it up
Good.. love the dishes here. Tasty ü§§

The jjajamyeon here is really the best I‚Äôve had in Singapore! Super flavourful and the noodles is nice and chewy. The sweet and sour pork is really good too. But it can be quite heavy to eat the entire plate to share between two pax. But definitely will be back

Ordered a bunch of food for takeaway, turned out they have missed an order despite the slow service and the little amount of people and orders from their takeaway board. I doesn't know how low standard this branch can gets but if Google review allows negative star this would be minus 2 star. They should have done their diligent can check the amountof food with the orders. Disappointed with swee choon for allowing their branches to provide substandard service.

Came on a Sat night and was pleasantly surprised by the quality of steak and value for money of this little gem tucked away in a housing estate. We had the platter to share which has 200g steak, 1/4 ribs, crispy chicken and sausages. Argentinean ribeye was delicious. Must be medium rare. The service is quick and food came out quickly. Don't forget about dessert as well. Definitely recommend for others to try this out.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Best XO fish beehoon! The fish was thick and meaty and the soup is packed full of flavours! My ultimate comfort food!
It's so salty that I need to clean away the sauce before eating. I even ordered an extra sauce..... haizzzz

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Economical Nasi Padang place for the people from nearby offices.  Might get very busy in lunch time. But the food is delicious and portion size is good.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The queue is really long at dinner time because there's only one service staff taking order before you can get seated. The ribeye was overcooked and dry and some parts were fully burnt. Their sides were at least edible. Astons used to be known for being value for money, but their standard has dropped drastically. Not an exaggeration that I've had steak at coffee shops nicer than this, and a third of Astons price.
Twice ive seen staff not wash their hands after using the toilet. Good luck

Ordered on grabfood. Was a very delightful meal. Had the tomyum soup which did not leave me thirsty and was a good balance of spicy and sour and the seafood was not mushy either. The vegetable had a sauce tht went well with the rice.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
We are their old regular customers for 3-4 years. My family ( 7+2 ) always spend hundreds of dollars per meal.

They make an mistake and served wrong food but expect us to pay. Even raised voice at us ‚Äú you ate the food, you need to pay‚Äù. If that‚Äôs the case, the staff shouldn‚Äôt even put the food on our table right? We even did the right thing by informing you that u served wrong however some of us ate it as we didn‚Äôt know what our dad ordered

Didn‚Äôt even bother to give discount or apologise. Btw that horfun worth$18 lol and taste super bland. There‚Äôs isn‚Äôt wok hey taste either. Definitely will never come back and support them.

Decided to try this place because of its reviews. Although the food is pretty decent, I found a total of 3 stands of hair inside my husband and my food. Needless to say I didn't finish my food. The waiter took away our food and acted dumbfounded. No apologies, no service recovery. Nothing. Not that all these matters... but sigh. Simply disappointed.

The atmosphere was calm and relax. The waiter/waitress were bubbly and friendly to all the customers. We had a great time and wonderful food during our last visit for my spouse's birthday celebration. As usual, a complimentary cake for the birthday person.
Over-rated and expensive. There are much better and cheaper Indian Rojak outlets in Yishun; Yishun Park Hawker Centre (NK), Chong Pang (Elahe)...

One of my favourite Â∑ùËèúÈ¶Ü„ÄÇLove their bbq sticks and also Ëæ£Â≠êÈ∏°. Price is reasonable. If you are coming on a weekdays, usually there is no queue. However, weekends recommended to book before coming. They have private room for booking too if you prefer to have some privacy. They also offer È∫ªËæ£È¶ôÈîÖ and other nice delicacies.
Decent food at affordable rates. A neat place for vegetarians too.

Brought my son for dimsum promo at 3.30pm... But disappointed that Xiao Long Bao and egg tarts are not available... These are what my son wants to eat... So ended up we didn't eat anything from dimsum menu...
One of the few places where you can find good and  affordable food in this neighborhood:) Staff are friendly too.

The location is now easily accessible by TEL Line. The Prata Blaster tasted great for someone who tries it out for the first time. On subsequent visits, it tasted a bit overwhelming for me. Decent pricing. A general go-to place to have Prata with family and friends.

Lot of varieties of western foods n Japanese like foods with a reasonable price... All rice come with a small bowl of a little diluted taste but overall it ok... Tried their pan fried fish with Japanese rice @ $4.80... fish is soft and well pan fried... Don't mind to come back again...

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content:
Claims to close at 11pm based on their google directory.

Went there at 9pm on a Saturday night and their staff already brought the barriers down and chased away customers.

Disappointed and will stop patronising this outlet.
1 stick for $1 lok lok! üòã The brocolli are a must-order!! The seasoning used is different from the other places I've tried as well, tasted more peppery than usual.
price is a little steep for food in a school establishment but overall decent baked pasta. would be great if there were a bit more ingredients :‚Äù) coffee was good though!
Happy with rice bowl.. thick and generous Sashimi... üëç
Alot of sauce to choose from and really reasonably priced. Opens till late too! Perfect for supper :)

Affordable Japanese Food, surprisingly good üëçüòã

Shall come back again, hoping for speedier Food wait
Went to United Square outlet. The staff is very friendly and helpful especially thanks to Choy Men for such a good service.
Cheap but scrumptious food highly recommended for south indian food lovers

Came for dinner in the middle of the week around 8pm. It wasn‚Äôt too busy. Service was prompt but not friendly. We were served nuts that you automatically get charged for if you don‚Äôt reject them... (traps for new players!), ditto if you ‚Ä¶

Really friendly staff that were willing to go through the menu. Main point though, the food is absolutely mind-blowing! Had their Roti Canai, Satti Sorru & the Commandoes, all just other worldly. The Commandoes though, a unqiue fry of sambal, ikan bilis, tauhu, fries and hotdogs might sound weird, but its worth more than a shot, and their curry was awesome!

Dear Patrons, thank you for your supportüòÄ I appreciate the two Stars review from you guys.
Thank you for the understanding and we will definitely improve to suit your taste buds! We welcome you back and get 1 free meal on usüòâ

This is my first time trying and it was totally horrible! Soup was salty and it just tasted awful even though I'm a fan of tomato soup. The vegetables and noodles were sticked together in the bowl like it was not well cooked and it was not warm. The wait was long even just for a bowl with no crowds and no napkins were served. Too bad I had to give 1 star to post if not I wouldn't give any star sorry to say.
Please don't try this dish üôèüôè
Good food, good prices and friendly service. I have eaten here several times and it's always good.
First & last time here. The prices are just as expensive albeit it being in a HDB. No government control this is what happens. Not for poor Merdeka/Pioneer  citizens like me.

Standards dropped a lot, and I mean a lot. Ordered chicken don earlier for lunch, waited for more than half an hour, yet rice is not fully cooked, chicken is either not fresh or not defrost well. Awful experience and probably not in my lunch list moving forward.
delicious food and great service from staff , definitely will come back again üëçüèªüëçüèª

Came in with decent expectation but was utterly disappointed by the quality and taste of the food :(

Sushi go, you have so much potential. I think you can do better.....

Fried Salmon skin very hard and clumped together.

The unagi thing really taste very creative/weird. Please don't.

Great food & service. They have promotion for crabs currently. Crabs are fresh and in decent size. Value for moneyüëçüòã. And whole rows of interesting food shops outside the restaurant including durian cake was good.  Will go again.

Ordered soup and dry noodle.
Noodles were very well cooked, Al dente.
Fishball was abit mushy, didnt quite suit my pallete.
Fishcake was brilliant thou, strong and bold taste.
Must be there before 10am if not highly likely will be sold out.
Would recommend the dry noodle over soup.
Best thosai.

Let's be fair and honest, the food quality has dropped due to the inflation and the spike rised of food cost, I can accept it, the most is visit lesser since there are other alternative around the corner, that's not my main focus today.

Something I want to highlight and cannot tolerate with, is the attitude of the staff at city square mall. I am a regular customer of Fei Xiong Group.
I always patrol their stalls at different places all over Singapore, specially Encik Tan at Vivo, Malaysia Boleh at AMK Hub and Jurong Point, Nam Kee Pao at Grandstand and Plaza Singapura and Malaysia Chiak at  Centre point, all the staff I have met never show any attitude problems so far except the branch at City Square Mall.

I have had encountered a few incidents prior to my sharing today. It was a very unpleasant experience and affected my lunching mood each time.

The staff I would like to bring to the attention is the staff in charge of Claypot rice/Bak Kut Teh, this man is always very rude and impatient while serving customers.

The other one is the staff preparing the wantoon noodle and ban mian, skinny male Malaysian who simply ignored my special order and showing sign of attitude.

This was what had happened, I discovered that I was paying $0.90 for my takeaway, hence clarified why not $0.60. after knowing that charged per container, I decided not to separate my noodle from the soup. He was a bit unhappy but refunded the $0.30. What made me feeling frustrated was my curry noodle was ready,  but he told me the ban mian wouldn't be ready so fast but have to wait, fineüôÑ.

So I stood aside, while waiting, I only saw one customer collected the wanton noodle, no one else. Next one was my turn, question is, why would he wants to delay my ban mian? Why can't he prepare both at the same time?

The worse thing is, after I reached home, I saw that the curry has nearly dried up due to the delay on the waiting time and I also didn't get the breast meat I specially ordered which he promised to serve, instead I got a chicken wing with 2 tao pok and two tiny pieces of long bean, which I really dislike chicken wings. Ended up I added luncheon meat to go with the beehoon.

I had the feeling that this staff did a "revenge" behind the scene to his customer after being requested a $0.30 refund and causing some trouble to him. Obviously this is an attitude problem!!!

The above scenario was only one out of the so many incidents I had encountered and why should I not sharing this with all of you so that I am not the only one but you can also try to experience it yourself. Good Luck!!
