So i am here quite regularly. The mala is spot on. Small spicy is plenty good enough for me
Today try set lunch where they get random stuff for you. Good bowl of stuff and i fully enjoyed it.
Fav mala in Singapore. Go for the fish, potato, chicken, pork, beef, vege, eggs, potatoes, lotus etc etc. All good. Maggie mee must take.
Also sell ice-cream so you can cool your mouth after.

Crab curry is very salty n fresh coconut served w hard flesh.
We order fish head n rice...reasonable price n yummy   w generous lady finger n brinjal.
Accessible by TEL just next door üëç

Used to love their fish n chips few yrs ago. But now the fish a bit fishy. Like that their fries r those thicker zigzag ones, the coleslaw taste good, nice garlic toast (fresh loaf kind). The fish n chip comes with a big slice of lemon. For $6.5, the portion is fair
Service is good, will keep remind you the new pour tea is hot.. food not bad and the food serving is fast. Place is clean and comfortable. Will come again

I went there in Valentine and ordered their Valentine special. The food is good and the portion is big for the price. Its worth it. But it a little bit crowded and the service is alittle slow, I think is due to the valentine day.
I waited for 15min before I get a table even through I booked a week earlier.
Takes a while for the food the come out. The plates are not clean. There was something stuck to my salmon sushi (not part of the dish). The food was subpar. 10/10 would NOT recommend.

At Meeras i always feel welcom with a warm smile.As drop by there for meals regularly they know me well.Food is willing cooked according to your taste bud ,if you asked for it.Good friendly staff.üôèüëç

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The food was delicious and the ambience was great! The staffs, especially Hock Seng, served us well and was friendly too! It was overall a nice experience üòÑüëçüèª
Come and try.. üëç
Ordered a chicken drumstick and 2 vegetable items and it cost $7.50. Taste was so so, I've had better for less elsewhere.
It will be good to have partition for smoking corner at Ang Mo Kio blk422.
Nice assortments of Rojak. Had nasi goreng merah (not bad). The mee kuah also good. Tried the chicken chop with fries too, a must try.
Nice food but the wait between dishes is too long because they gave priority to takeaway like Grab, food panda, deliveroo ... etc.

First time bought takeaway from this shop.  Most of the prata (eggs and plain) they gave me is burned.  How to eat like that. Terrible. This type of burned prata should go to the dustbin but they sold to takeaway orders which we can't feedback on the spot.  We threw most of the prata away. Worst prata and will be my last visit.

The best chicken Rice! There are many chicken rice stalls in Singapore  as it is a common dish Singaporeans have in our daily life. This stall to me, their way of making the Rice is the best! It is frangrance, not too oilly, and it packed in a bowl. You could simple eat it by itself without other dishes. The chili also very good! When people eat chicken rice,  another important factor is their Chicken rice chili. It is make with the chicken oil that come out when boiling the chicken and their special ingredient.  The chicken is tender and juicy, but not especially good. Usually they serve only the chili and dark black soya sauce, but you can and shold ask for ginger! This is traditional chicken stalls will serve. It blend very well with chili and black soya sauce also on chicken rice.

The other dishes that serve in the restaurent are well cook and delicious. They serve one traditional dish that is pig livers in clay pot, today you hardly find this dish. It is nice and smell really great with garlic. Another dish you may want to try is their deep fried toufu, its crispy and hot, it taste so good when u eat while it hot.

Was expecting a normal Japanese meal, turns out to be a great meal that must share to friends!
Ordered the saba shio fish, Koebi (fried small prawns) kake udon, and okonomiyaki. All were delicious and very much like having a meal back in Japan! Portions were bigger than expected, but value for money!
Had hot barley tea, came in a big pot, bf got iced one, free refills! Must come and try, won't be disappointing!
Do wish it's more accessible, have to drive in or change buses.
tast good cheep fast

My first time eating here and the San Lou hor Fun was superb! Portion was huge for $7, value for money!! The home-made barley drink wasn‚Äôt too sweet, just right! Will definitely come back again!! Highly recommended!!
Delightful d√©cor and scrumptious meals. Quick service. Robot waiter available with trays.

Nice Indian food. Particular love the potato cutlet, mutton and their dhal. However do note that they will close their kitchen from 3.00 to 5.30pm and between that period can only order from the counter. Do note your visit timing to avoid disappointment.
Super nice environment with great vibes! Prefect to bring your date here. Highly recommend 10/10 MUST TRYYY!!

The signature is the pork chop with mushroom sauce. Sauce is good and the pork is also grill nice and fresh and so it taste good

Order fish and chips and lamb chop before. Both are not bad but still lose the pork chop.

The fries are quite bland with no salt taste so recommend to add cheese

Portion are huge and most cannot finish for most people

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Seafood jjumpong is very delicious, strongly recommend. Visited few times never disappointed. Another dish that impressed is spicy jellyfish salad, really yummy.

King of Fried Rice disappointing.
Rice did not have any flavour and even though it smells nice, the rice is completely bland and not worthy of a trip there.

Quality Xing Hua food at affordable prices, food servings were just like their other outlets. Service was well trained and had celebrated our gathering successfully. Definitely to come here again soon.
Average mee rebus only. Too watery for my liking.
Service and food in the restaurant is good. But prices are expensive. Even after student and staff discount, its very expensive.

Seriously one of the nice cosy Japanese foodie place!!!!
The food was good !!! The service excellent!!! Crazy ambiance
Must come and don‚Äôt gonothe replace in that street

Nice place. Set menu are worth it. Meat quality is top notch! Smoke free BBQ. Won‚Äôt let you leave smelling like a bbq grill. Meat is juicy and tender after grilling. Top with rice and let the fats drip into the rice. Set comes with choice of salad or kimchi. Drinks are not included. Soup is included in set. Economical pricing. Choose from basic set menu or premium set menu for better quality meat. No bookings. Walk in only and expect queue during peak hours. Definitely 1 of my favourites now!

The food was very light. Compared with the usual Chinese Asian dishes the food tastes more like home cooked dishes done by your grandma. Not very flavourful but not bad in general. Simply put it nothing really stands out much, but it‚Äôs a cozy place to have home made food. The only downside was probably the heat inside. The aircon was not working even though there are two. We kept sweating during the dinner. Hope it can be fixed.

I just to brought 2 package of rice. 1 is duck and the other one is chicken rice. I ask for the sambal chili the boss keep insist say no . I say I exchange for the sambal she shouted very loud SAY NO. she say that chili only for noddle I keep telling her I exchange she just SAY NO NONO. Omg I will never go back again anymore.

Ordered fried fish, bee hoon and lor mee.. nice.
Chrysanthemum tea niice too!!
Downside is just a bit too hot.
Food still good like before. No need to go Putien
Our favourite place for delicious crispy prata. The prata is made only when we order so it's always fresh and warm. This outlet has indoor and outdoor seating.

We come here for CNY reunion lunch every year. The food items taste good. The prawns are exorbitant in prices but I guess it‚Äôs the same for all seafood items in Chinese restaurants during cny. I would have given this full marks if not for the Nian Gao. It‚Äôs not fried and it taste very sweet and strange. I find the mango sago very sweet as well. Service is good as usual!
Simple zi char, decent portion sizes. Sambal belacan chilli is good.
Food was ok, felt the serving was less for a table of 10pax..Place was big to hold big events.The speaker volume was quite loud. Could have volume down abit.
A bit too salty for me personally, but considering the price and the place,  this place is good for quick meals.
Their stir fried combo of 3 whites: flat rice noddle (hor fun), sliced fish and bean sprouts is up to standard.

We initially thought the prices to be on the high side but the portions turned out to be very generous, we had difficultly finishing our food. Fish was very sweet and fresh and the aburi and eel slices were seasoned with yuzu, making them very tasty. I think I won't bother heading to The Sushi Bar anymore as this place is so near my place.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Taste is above average. Worth a try. However, the quantity is on the low side.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
Super Authentic Thai food prepped by Thai chefs.
I am glad to find this here in Singapore.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content:
Monday lunch, 4 pax.
The guest room in the restaurant is amazing, spacious and have a good sense of privacy.
Food is very up to standard and authentic. P.S. I‚Äôm from Hunan myself.
Amazing springleaf pizza , great drinks and nice atmosphere.
I ordered truffle beef rice from foodpanda and it was so nice and flavorful. I will definitely recommend my friends and order again!

I think 1 of the staff like over workload because he is the one packing grab order (i saw like large order)/cut sushi and he also the one taking order...
another one look like only know how to assembly the food... he just stand there and see only...

Pasta portion was okay, but not worth the steep price of $8+ . When compared to competitors nearby, you can certainly get better value for your money from elsewhere. For a baked pasta, it certainly could use more cheese. Prices are not student-friendly.
Meatball was tasty, a 3/5.  But other than that flavour-wise, the pasta was a 2/5.
Overall, the pasta tastes almost like what you would expect to find from 7-11 or cheers but less flavourful and at double the price. (although the portion here is slightly more)
Surprisingly, the curly fries are exceptional good
Yes glutinous rice was well prepared...coupled with same other sushi delights

Been there afew times, both dine in & takeout.  The crab promo is a good deal. Their crabs are fresh & of good quality, especially loving their black pepper crab. Their hor fun is good too. Their price is reasonable and no service charge if you dine in. Free milk tea if you order for takeaway.

I like the prata. Tad bit expensive than kopitiam but in exchange you have an air condition place to dine in.

Edit - recently went there for something other than prata and the fried rice is rather decent. The same can't be said for the tom yum.

We waited for about 45mins. But the staff did warn us before we order. Friendly staff took order at the cashier. Note they do not serve ice with soft drinks.

Overall food is nice.
Spaghetti serving was huge! Forgot to take a pic though.

Five of us had the Xmas menu. Pretty disappointing as the portions were quite small and food quality was so so. I used to like Xi Yan a lot but haven‚Äôt had a chance to go back since Covid. But I realised the quality and food portions has shrunk considerably. We are not big eaters but despite a 6 course lunch, we still felt like we were not full. Hope that they do improve but hard for me to revisit again for the quality at this price point.

Hearty tzi-char fare. Dishes came in decent sized portions, flavourful but not overly salty...packed with wokhei. Found that their popular 'sam lo hor fun' was just average, a little too dry for my liking. Otherwise prices are reasonable (but on the higher end of the scale) and have a good selection of items. Was there around 7.30pm on a tues and place was quite filled. Food was served after about 20min wait.
First time here, fish head curry, it is $24 but pretty tasty. Brinjal and okra is cooked through. The tomato tasted a little weird. The tofu with enoki dish is pretty good too.
Nice Chinese food.

I like the second day cny gathering. The booking a week ago for us is 1045 to 12 cos others booked earlier got 12 o'clock slot. As this is cny period any slot is good for us cos we just need a place to eat with iur loved ones. The food is average but the memory lingers a long time.
Nice restaurant in NTU. Food is good. Recommended.

Delicious assam laksa ($4.50) that brought be back to Penang for a brief moment at the first spoonful of broth. Generous with the vegetables and mint atop the addictive rice noodles. Could have been more generous with the fish, but still very satisfying overall!

Jack‚Äôs Place has been around for a long, long while. But it seems food quality has dropped slightly over the years, albeit the food is still good and value for money.

The garlic bread wasn‚Äôt as crisp as usual, ie it was sagging a bit under its own weight. But it still tasted okay.

The lobster bisque and the soup of the day (minestrone) were both nice.

The steaks weren‚Äôt that juicy, to be honest. But they were still well cooked and seasoned, so they were still great.

The baked potatoes were extremely filling, but still tasted good.

The dessert was a cherry and mango pie, which was pretty nice.

All in all, the food was pretty average, the main draw being the value for money it allows.

However, the service was top notch, being extremely prompt and friendly to boot. (This may have been because I arrived at 11am, before peak lunch time).

Overall, the food is just like any other Jack‚Äôs Place, but the service is prompt, genuine and doesn‚Äôt leave you with a bad taste in your mouth.

Had the T bone set for 2.. the waiting time was definitely not 30min as stated. It took close to an hr for the meat to be served. Sides were generous and we were honestly already full from them while waiting for the main.
Sides (potatoes & macncheese) were great but the T bone was extremely tough and not tasty at all..

Maybe because they were understaffed... I went there to dine for mother's day dinner with my mother. I reserved a table but they didn't seem to have my name on the reservation list? All the waiters were too busy to be flagged down. Clearing of plates was done when they happened to walk past the table, just the arm stretched in, take the plates and walk off. No asking " Is it okay if I clear the table". Had 2 items the waiters forgot to bring to us... which took a while for us to get them because the waiters were so hard to flag. In the end, we got some good service from the assistant manager.

Very disappointed version of Penang Prawn Noodle. Other than the taste was bad, the served bowl of prawn noodle is so far different compared to the photo being displayed. Chendol was diluted. Too much ice but too less coconut milk. It‚Äôs like drinking super diluted coconut milk water. Rojak was just below overage of sg rojak as only can taste rojak sauce but can‚Äôt taste any prawn paste in the rojak. Overall this establishment is a disgrace to Malaysia food. Malaysia Chiak indeed poorly representing Malaysian food.
Food was really good and value for money. Owner is friendly and helpful

The fish head steamboat is a must try, ideal for 4 pax or more. Comes with Groupa or promfet (scan QR picture to check food and dim sum.menus), fish bones are deep fried before stewing in the pot, heated by charcoal. Side plate of nai nai veggies, enoki mushrooms and fried egg. Service staff attentive, keeps on topping up soup base.

You can order dim sum or from a la carte or set meal.
Prices went up is understandable but not food quality. Before $7.80 for katsu don compared to $8.90 now is a lot diff.
Small plates. Good prices. Pretty good food. Good for a quick bit. The jasmine tea is really good.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Bad attitude counter girl ask me to wait but didn't expect at more than 45 mins for 3 items. When I ask them to escalate my orders, one girl asked me to go to kitchen and check myself. Terrible! Only one nice lady did hear my complains and apologized. Been a pure vegetarian, totally disappointed with such attitudes in the shop.

It don't even deserve one star at all. Lousy attitude especially from Char Kway Teow stall guy who just care more about looking at his hp then cooking. Know it could be due to high rental but the portion is just miserably small and the taste just doesn't do Malaysian food justice. Definitely 1 of the worst food places that I have been to. üò°

Cozy place where you can get authentic Shanghainese food!

Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâÂåÖ($2.50 each), Êò•Âç∑ ($6) and ÈÜâÈ∏° ($10) are must try on the menu! Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ was nicely done, the pork belly was really soft and tender. Dip the fluffy bun into the sauce for a greater gastronomical experience! The crispy Êò•Âç∑ and its flavourful filling goes perfectly well with vinegar. ÈÜâÈ∏° was very juicy and there‚Äôs a lightly gelatinous feel to it. You can taste the booziness of the Ëä±ÈõïÈÖí, definitely better than DTF‚Äôs version!

We pre-ordered ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖ ($6) when making our reservation. Bite with caution as the scalding soup bursts right through the bun. My family loved it but I guess I just don‚Äôt enjoy pan fried buns that much.

We also tried ‰∏äÊµ∑Â∞èÈ¶ÑÈ•® ($3.50), my to-go breakfast when I‚Äôm in Shanghai. I absolutely loved it, even though it‚Äôs just wanton soup to most people.

Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖ($6), a tad bit saltier than DTF‚Äôs, but more flavourful with a more chewy skin. I liked it and thought it was better than DTF‚Äôs, albeit sadly, there‚Äôs no ginger slices to go with it.

Ended the dinner with ÂçóÁìúÈ•º ($2.50 each) and ÈÖíÈÖø‰∏∏Â≠ê($3). Loved the chewy ÂçóÁìúÈ•º that had red bean fillings.

ÈÖíÈÖø‰∏∏Â≠ê really fell short of expectations, cos my grandma used to make this at home. The glutinous rice ball was great (I love all mochis) but the rice wine was too diluted hence resulting in a watery rice wine soup. Could be better if it were more starchy and add more rice wine.

Overall still a great dinner and I‚Äôll be back to try the noodles next time!

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Bad experience today around 11.30am, ordered 2 bowl of fish soup noodles , waiting for almost After 40min wait , asked the waitress abt my order of two bowls of soup noodles She was rude to say that I need to wait longer. But  I saw they served those expensive dishes 1st to the customers that came later than us . My point is they need to inform customers about the long waiting time before they take orders. Don‚Äôt let customers wait for too long as they may have other appointments.
One of my fav go to Thai food! Friendly prices but sometimes the wait can be long but totally worth it
Reasonably priced food. However, fried dim sum is at best average.
Delicious food and well presented. Staff were helpful and the dishes came out quite quick one after another.

The spoons were dirty, came with small pieces of what looked like leftover food‚Ä¶ Chawanmushi is decent. Tonkatsu ramen tasted like cup noodles. Can be better! But reasonably priced and service staff helpful.

It's a nice place to dine in with the family. There's a great variety of chinese/cantonese-style food to please everyone in my family, from my parents-in-law to my young children. And I love that they now cater to vegetarians too by including a number of great vegetarian dishes in their menu.

Truly an iconic stall in the west. Be sure to get your breakfast here.

Nasi sambal goreng was really nice. Serunding and sambal were sweet but that‚Äôs ok.

Had dinner last time here. I am pleased with the excellent service. The staffs are very attentive in the name of Ivy Zhang .Table settings are nice and clean. The Foods are great and amazing. I will visit it again soon. Enjoyed it so much. Im giving 5 star. Would recommend it to friend's. ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
Very enjoyable meal in a clean well managed restaurant with lovely friendly staff. We had  ginger chicken, fried rice and a couple of other vegetable dishes, all delicious üôå
Enjoy my lunch here.
Serving good Tze Char dishes. Need to go earlier to avoid the queues.
Interesting! A great way to bond with colleagues! Kudos Social Kitchen!

The assam fish head has the right amount of spicy heat but could be a little more salty for my personal taste preference. The sweet and sour pork is nice and I liked the broccoli. The rest if the food is good but not spectacular. Serving size is generous.
We had lunch for 3 person on 31.1.2022. The chicken rice taste was average. Pricy.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Love the yummy fish soup with milk and wine! All - time favourite! Only setback is the parking nearby are limited

The buffet is terrible and disappointing, small portion, served dishes very slow and didn't serve dishes like prawns and pork in the end, moreover they deleted the negative comments on Facebook page to hide the truth, horrible

Eaten sambal chicken biryani. Sambal sauce salty too the max. Chicken too tough, leftover chicken???üòëüòëüòë
$9 for a no standard briyani. Next time pls never bring me here againüòñ
Food is less oily and salty than others, while the sauces are just decent. 1hr queue to select the sticks you want; another 1 hr wait for the sticks to be cooked. Be prepared to wait!

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: It's not bad but pricey

Food is adequately fresh
Good service!
Friendly staffs. Dishes are delightful. The chicken is one of the best I've had.
This Western Food used to be very nice. But after the owner employ helper to do the cooking, the chicken wing sometimes is not fully cook. üëéüëéüëé
Prata is freshly made n relatively bigger. üëç Yummy
Yummy fish soup thats full of flavor yet light at the same time. This is one of my favorite fish soup place in Tanjong Pagar area

A mini version of Beauty in a Pot, where each can order and individual hotpot. However, the good thing was is not like everyone has to order one hotpot, and two can actually share 1 too. No collagen broth but quite a few other flavours (more than Beauty), and ordered the ginseng chicken soup which was flavourful. The Tang O was very fresh and gave the soup an additional kick. Meat wise was also fresh. While I wouldn't say this is a budget friendly younger sibling of Beauty in a Pot, as the bill still came up to about $80+ for two. However, still worth to visit once in a while and especially if you are not planning in advance but kinda want it last minute.
Amazing event team offering a range of cooking lessons, super organised and the recipes are easy to follow!
Decent ramen at much more affordable prices. They also give the additional noodles.  Good service. Can save time by ordering online then collect at store.

Service is more of a miss recently, and I feel the food standards have dropped tremendously of late.

The most disappointing thing is having 3 wait staff insist that it's "normal" for fried food to come drenched in oil. The paper liner is glazed full of oil.

Similar to our recent previous visit, I've also had to repeatedly chase the servers for status for the 1 last dish. It's really odd how they leave one last dish hanging like that, we just sat around having finished everything we've ordered but waiting for that one *final* dish.

Always visited in the morning ala carte dimsum period, but I guess not anymore.

Great food. Reasonable prices. Unusual but pleasant location. Nice ambience. Very gracious hosts. Dont forget to return your used plates after your meal to the inside as they have few staff only and you dont want to attract the pigeons, do you?

Had Prata and Tea here!!! Highly recommended. The oil used in the preparation is fresh. Order taking is promptly attended to and payment is straightforward. Most important.... Reasonably priced. Awesome breakfast place on a Saturday morning. Located at Springleaf MRT station.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
I order la mian beef with spicy soup.
But I think this is pork belly.
No more photo in the menu .

Best chicken cutlet and chop in Ang Mo Kio, some says North east as well. Great seasoning, generous portion and fast service. The lamb chop are good too! Highly recommended if you are around the area.
Provide Very traditional Chinese food. Take away offer is so worth and delicious.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Food is absolutely delicious, 10/10. üëç

Do try their Briyani sets or Vegetarian Thali set, with Masala Spiced Tea üòã
One of my favorite western food places. Affordable and taste great! There's always a queue but kitchen is quick with orders.

Revisited after a l.o..n...g break, glad to find both quality & service remain par to early days, stiffer price tags understandable espy., being niche Izakaya üèÆ over ulu-part of western region.

Love the wide array of sakeüç∂ & shochuü•É.
Cozy and warm. Staff nice. Price is reasonable. Food is very good. Can recommend to host a lunch or dinner.

The quality of the food is always constant. Even with the crowd, the servers tried their best to serve with a smile. With a Chinese restaurant setup, always have promos on-going, it is definitely worth it to dine with friends anf and family.
Ordered a few times, the food quality and taste is not as good as the Waterway Point one. Really annoying that most of the restaurants in Sengkang taste awful.

The food was good. The restaurant was cosy. And the portions seemed generous enough for us. Maybe we are small eaters or used to pricey food. But we didnt expect the serving sizes to be what they were for the price we paid. Will go again!

Out of all the halal ramen, this so far is pretty close, especially the beef sukiyaki! Soy sauce flavour and decent amount of fat‚ô° the soup, noodles and toppings were good and the egg was marinated well in the soy, albeit the yolk was not runny. Still delicious nonetheless.

Their breakfast porridge was alright, tasted like a oyakodon porridge. Char siew beef ramen was alright, and their beef donburi was generous! And their matcha was really good!! Thick and full of matcha flavour and you can feel the powder. The ice cream was also great. Matcha pudding was very bitter by itself but paired with its brown sugar sauce was delicious. The only thing that was subpar that I ate was the salmon sashimi. But I'd definitely return for their ramen‚ô°‚ô°‚ô°

The service was really friendly and quick and helpful! Atmosphere was really nice aswell.

The waitress was polite and the service was fine. The "chef" was smoking outside when we arrived and when we left the place.

On a Saturday 11am they were out off burgers ALREADY. Really?
I do not know if they really did not have the meat or if they wanted to make us order something more expensive.
Not bad. Often buy thosai for breakfast.

Truly excellent nasi Padang. The meats and the curries are Super consistent and wonderful. Be sure to try their beef rendang and bergedil. Be sure to say yes when they offer you their chilli on the side!

Only thing that isn‚Äôt consistent is the price. I order the same thing at every visit, but hardly ever get charged the same price.
Yay, fun!
Food quality has been consistent but soft skill of staff lacking over years. Unlike in their earlier days, staff are super attentive.

After a long tiring day I was super hungry wanted something nice to eat. It was already 8:30pm. I ordered Udang Satti Sooru and nandu rasam. The food came and it's safe to say I was a happy child after the 1st bite. I slept like a Snorlax..

I love the food here and the quiet cosy ambience. My then fiance randomly searched for a nearby venue for our wedding lunch reception and found this place. We have dined here several times and always good.

First time buying from them.  Too costly.  This is the first and last.  Will never patronise this restaurant anymore.  Just ask for some mutton cubes take away. Mostly $5.50.  Very very small portion ,a lot potato. 4 to 5 cubes mutton only. I was charged $8.50.   It‚Äôs take away. Not dine in.  Service charge??  Mostly I buy dum briyani from. Al haldeera Restsurant located at Toa Payoh interchange , basement.  Lots of rice. Boiled egg with papadam plus some salad bonless mutton and dalcha gravy.  It‚Äôs $8 to $9 only.  And the food taste so gd.  But at this amk.  Really disappointed and this is not the way to do buisness.  I took some photos of the portion of mutton will post it.  Pls pls. Think before dinning in or take away from this restaurant.  Cut throat.
The food comes out really slow. Several tables who ordered after us got their food really quickly even though we ordered the same thing.

Nice and spacious cafe in the quiet Sembawang Hills with friendly staff. Seems to be pet-friendly with many customers with dogs out front.

Had typical cafe food with some interesting twists e.g. Nacho Cheese on Wagyu Burger, Rose Matcha Latte. However feels slightly pricy, even for a cafe, (~$20), especially if you order cmmon cafe food

Would recommend to try if you're in the area, and get the more special foods on the menu (like Otah Bruschetta) instead of things like the typical American Breakfast set.

Haven't been here for a while. Good quality food at reasonable prices. Family had an enjoyable and fulfilling meal. Steak and deep fried food were great! If anything, the ribs needed more sauce and the seafood baked rice wasn't that tasty.

Had a sumptuous breakfast: Lamb Shank, Egg Prata and Teh Halia.  The lamb shank is huge with chunky meat packed with spicy favours.  Egg Prata is crispy and yummy. However, the ginger milk tea lacks the punchy favour.  Friendly and prompt services made a pleasant dining experience.  Will sure be back.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Stall looks clean. Nasi lemak Chilli is nice. And also ayam taliwang chilli, consider spicy. There's another ayam balado chilli, is more spicy, try if u like spicy

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
The menu has a lot of variety. The waiter was patient to recommend less spicy options for me and spicy ones for my family member.

We ordered butter chicken naan set and mutton naan set. Both were delicious! The Masala tea was very good!!  Prices were reasonable too.

The owner was friendly and we look forward to our meals at her restaurant again.
Nice place to get catch up with friends. Saw a lot of parents bring kids to see the fun train delivery of food.
An Absolute Hidden Gem In e Neighbourhood I Would Say... e Food Is Great & Definitely Worth e Prices!! You'll Never Regret Trying... I'll Definitely Be Back Again~ üòãüòãüòãüçªüçªüçª

Tried the Karubi and Harami set. Meat is well marinated and the sauce complements it quite well. Quite a huge serving of rice for the sets - that's what makes you full after perhaps 200g of meat.

Order is done via scanning a QR code and submitting your choices via a webpage. The buzzer on your table will ring when your food is ready for collection. Payment is made via a kiosk at the exit. This self-service concept is different from other outlets. It's slightly weird because most of the staff are just standing around doing nothing most of the time.

Update Jul 2022: The staff will bring the food to your seat when it's ready. However there's a long wait for the food after you place the order.
Prompt service. Been to this outlet a few times even during weekday dinner, no crowd. The food was quite standard. Love their chawanmushi thou

Third time dining here and excellent as always. They serve wonderfully authentic, home-style Indian classics and they have also started serving a new Penang food range which is amazing as well. We ordered Pratas and Chapatis to mop up the flavourful curries on this visit and they were perfect.Our new favourite Indian food joint. Our family of 10 left with full tummies and big smiles. Superb value for money as well. Happy days!!

Edit: Came by again on 25 Apr 21 and the food was amazing still. Satti Sorru, Sambal Seabass, Prawn Sothi and Chicken 65 we all executed perfectly. Fully recommended.

Very polite and helpful staff. Food was decent. Game chicken was moist and juicy, even the breast meat (and I'm normally wary of eating chicken breast because it usually comes overcooked). Truffle fries were good. My sister's fish and chips turned out pretty well too!

We ordered 4 dishes to share for 2 pax. Yangzhou Fried rice was a decent one, not as tasty as the famous DTF style but still acceptable.  I was very delighted when I see they have this Qi cai dumplings Ëç†ËèúÈ¶ÑÈ•®Á∫¢Ê≤πÊäÑÊâã, but the taste is not what I expected, skin too thick. Both my colleague and me found it good was the drunken chicken (with strong shaoxing wine taste) and the duo fried dumplings (prawns and pork). Service was good, hope they maintain it. We spend $32.20 for this meal, without beverages.

Tasty food that feels home made at reasonable pricing.

Love the samsui chicken, eggplant claypot, broccoli with mushroom and beancurd skin and deep fried fish belly. Nothing lacking on food at all.

The service was also very prompt. The cashier somehow remembered my name at my second visit, which was impressive. The staff is also responsive and attentive to your requests.

Definitely a place to return for many years ahead.
Delightful fishball noodles in Malaysian style. Fishballs are self made. Simply unique and delicious. Good to be there no later than 11am to avoid sold out disappointment.
go this place enjoy it's vary good restaurant and bar

Tucked away on the 2nd floor, this place offers a wide variety of cuisines from Indian to Western and Korean.

This place also has a cloud kitchen that allows you to order and pickup certain food easily via their lockers but is however strictly for takeaways.

First time there - looks extremely popular at lunch. May need reservations at lunch.  Two of us, their specialty was the curry fish head and a plate of veg, and two hot drinks -$50.  Seems a tad expensive for half a head which was a little small to me.  Forgot to take the pics of the food.

Will try to bring my larger family here and give it a go- seems to have a variety of dishes.
Consistent long queue but moves fast. Worth the wait. Mee Rebus gravy is rich and creamy

McDonald's food with good standard, will keep up with outlets outside NTU and have the new menus. My only complaint is that it is always crowded during lunch time, but it shows it's popularity. Remember to ask for more chilli if you need.

Highly recommended!
Went on 24/09/2022, the Chicken curry Chee Cheong Fun is very nice, tasty curry gravy, the rojak is very delicious, also recommend curry me, tasty curry gravy and it's very big portion & many ingredients. Also recommend Ipoh Coffee.
Overpriced food , staff is rude , food menu is limited , most of the food is not available

Bad attitude. Rude staff taking orders. Please put someone more suitable in the service line and train your staff not to talk bad about customers in front of them. Not all customers can speak or understand mandarin. Thanks.

Mixed bowl noodles, is taste-less and not the mushroom cut until so thin slice. A bowl of the noodles with 2 bird egg, 2 slice of fish 2 pieces of prawn.... etc and drinks add up to be about $17. Which is not worth the money.
The staff there rejected rudely from counter shout to the table "sorry, cannot" As they don't allow outside food although she have family members eating inside.

Was cycling casually with buddies till we were so hungry, we decided to stop for food at this industrial coffee shop. After reckying all the fancies big signboard, we decided to settle with this Smallest signboard that says ‚ÄúMookata Lor‚Äù since we havnt had Mookata for quite awhile. And also like their ‚ÄúSinglish Thai‚Äù signboard name.

And tell you what.. Their ingredients had caught me by surprise.

- Their Prawns & Scallops were so fresh, so fresh like it‚Äôs straight from the sea. Giant Scallop were bigger than our old sg 50 cents coin.

- I personally do not like pork alot due to the pork smell but trust me, I had so much pork than I could imagine here.

- Chicken were well marinated & savory. Tender & Juicy.

- Beef is Goooood. I cant have enough of it. OMG I‚Äôm hungry again writing this review.

- Soup base was FANTASTIC. Well broth with tint of sweetness. Unlike many stalls we went, starts with plain water.

- Mookata cant go without condiments. They provides 3 different type of dips or you could create your own.
Thai dip is good, goes well with everything. Traditional mince garlic chilli padi with parsley, my favourite. Another was abit sweet, mild spicy perfect for non spicy takers. Gosh, spoilt for choices.

- Last thing I would like to emphasis is the price. All 3 of us had satisfied tummies at just less than 50 dollars.

We had a GREAT time GREAT meal at Mookata Lor yesterday evening. I had it pinned and will DEFINITELY visit again. A GEM we accidentally found.

Dont wait. Bring your whole family there now.
Food was good!
it is family feast for us. EVERYTHING WAS GREAT. MUST TRY PLACE. very nice. everything was delicious and the delivery was fast. SAMBAL FISH MUST TRY.
From the very best SOTO Ayam stall in the world ! Well known too for hai Mee rebus power and Satay, this stall has been my TOP fav since school days . Do support them !
Not bad in term of taste and quality, but a bit pricey. Total cost is $80.15 for these 4 items plus an onsen egg.
The kitchen that looks like a makeshift kitchen shouldn‚Äôt be used at all. There‚Äôs no proper ventilation and the setup is a mess.
tried it 3 times. their pork chop ($7) was quite hard. chicken chop taste better. i dun eat beef but ppl who ordered beef makes mi drool. it smells heavenly.

Five stars for ambience and portion size!

The Malayan Council at Windstedt is all about the vibes, an atmosphere so nice you‚Äôll definitely enjoy chilling there.

Food portion was HUGE, it was our first time there and we definitely ate our fill, have two mains along with drinks and a complimentary side!

Service was good, food tasted good and we even got complimentary cakes to bring home. Price point definitely worth a mention, this place is good for occasions as it‚Äôs on the high side. Definitely fitting for occasions! :)
Decent taste thai food
Good food

D best green nasi lemak at yishun area and the price is affordables ($3 ) from schoolchildren to old folks.
The ingredients consist of 3 items to choose off such as chicken wing/fish/egg/fishcake/sausage or tempeh(fried soya)....but the chilli a bit sweet.
The peanut is anchovies is crispy.
Its still ok as it serves different level of individual taste.
The epok potato & sardine is ohhsome.
Overalls its is recommended.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Prata was decent.
Teh Tarik was the BOMB. This is as good as the legit teh tarik!!

Place is open 24/7 so good supper place. A pity that its air con place feels very oily, they need some ventilation. Rather they have more outdoor seats though.

Easy to find parking since theres a HDB carpark. Bro is v friendly too!

Had the mushroom linguine, mentaiko fries and spinach pasta. Enjoyed all of them. Portion size was good, mentaiko was very flavourful and had a torched flavour. Mushroom linguine had a generous amount of mushrooms and they were cooked well without too much of an earthy taste.

Could improve the acoustics in the restaurant though as there were not many people but it was very noisy. Good place to hold events but if it's so echoey it will not be conducive.

Do check out the well. It had a few dead leaves though. And the door to the back garden was locked.

Also there was a super smiley server, she was really cheerful, wish all servers were like her.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The staffs were attentive and topped up the food regularly. The meat were tasty too!

Very clean restaurant with good air conditioning, no food smell stain after visit.
The curry for the masala dosai was delicious.
Teh halia is totally not up to standard.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Good overall taste good, but the attitude not very nice  and service of the staff is slow
Good food for the price
Very bad service. Rude owners, bad attitude
The prata is freshly made dishes are delicious

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
Excellent nasi lemak eatery. The quality is one of the best around compared to other popular ones like Crave or Qiji.

The rice is especially fragrant and moist. The chicken leg is very tender and tasty. The fish is also very large size and overall for the price, it‚Äôs value for money.
service super average, food is also typical. do note many prices have inflated, and there‚Äôs no more free mentai sauce! go to remain the genki roll and mentaiko trio salmon, cant go wrong
Super legit halal donburi. Tried the unagi tamago, as well as their miso soup. Yum.

Terrible experience and customer service!
3 of us went and restaurant was kinda full, there was an empty small round-shaped table available but the waitress did not invite us in, we assumed it was being reserved. Waited at the door for around 15-20 minutes, another group of 6 queued behind us and obviously did not made a reservation, but was being invited in directly. When we asked the waitress, she replied because they can use the round-shaped table, and wanted us to wait for another smaller square-shaped table, with the customers still eating half way and who looked like gonna take at least 15-20 minutes to finish eating. We turned around and left, totally disappointed with this kind of service, and the waitress looked like she couldn't be bothered more.
Great job in prioritizing profit maximization rather than customer's experience! Will not recommend anyone to patron this restaurant!
I have been here a few times and each time the food quality never disappoint. Simple yet tasty food. Will come back again!
Authentic Thai food with no service charge and GST.

Located on the second story above Giant supermarket, you have to look for the stairs in the center of the building. There is a long queue and it starts from the stairs. We waited for about 35 minutes in the morning for the ala carte dim sum. You can order Teochew dishes from 11am onwards. There is a high tea dim sum buffet from 3-5pm.

The restaurant is spacious, have more than 50 seats and can serve large crowds. Ordering of food is done from the dim sum pushcarts when the staff pushes them around, told us what they have and asked if we want any. You can check with them if they have any of the items you want to order on their pushcarts. Staff was friendly and service was good and fast.

It is a nice experience to get the food like in the authentic Hong Kong dim sum restaurants, but you can't explore all the dishes as you do not know the menu / the dishes available and their prices. From what we spent, the dim sum is about $5.80 per item on average. The steamed items are cheaper than the fried ones.

SHINJITSU RAMEN.332 Ang Mo Kio Ave 1. Happened to come across this place after sending my dog for grooming a few doors away. We ordered the Tonkotsu ramen. The soup base is very rich with creamy texture. Two large pieces of very lean chashu and the hosomen or thin noodles is firm and tasty. This is their cheapest ramen at $6.90 per bowl. I give it a score 8/10. Will come back to try the other dishes like pork gyozs , chicken teriyaki stick, etc.

Poor customer service, they did not wear mask like seriously. I should have taken a photo and send to food safety inspector. Rude staff I said I want lontong then she said I said rice then she argue with me. Seriously lol dont eat there spoiled my morning.

The ribeye is pretty good
They serve with hot plate like in higher class restaurant
Overall pretty worth

Visited them on consecutive Sat and Sun! Service staffs are friendly and polite. Ordered their mushroom risotto and truffle fries for both days. It was really good! Amazingly, their coffee was a gem for us. We didn‚Äôt have high expectations on their coffee yet it was the star for our brunch. The sea salt caramel latte was da bomb! Not sweet yet very smooth and produce good aroma of the coffee. Will bring our kiddos back for the food!

Newly opened outlet. Great environment, great service and great food. Peking duck was very good. Good to order it in advance or you'll have to wait for 45 mins. The wagyu beef cubes  with truffle oil is a must try. The nai bai with sakura prawns was very good too.

Good to make a reservation. 69922777.
Food was ok. Ambient was a bit dark for our liking. Sushi/bento/ramen/udon quite a selection of Japanese dishes.

Talk about kicking it old school and going through a timewarp.. dang...

The service is great. Food is delish.
But really like timetravelling lol

I am glad they reopen after a fire burnt this coffee shop. After renovations, the stall front looks brighter. But the best thing about Chester Express is the healthy options. I asked for grilled chicken chop without sauce. I also ordered steamed vegetables (broccoli) and garden salad without sauce. And they did it perfectly without mistake. Great for healthy diet
I have always received excellent service from Bo Bo. She is very knowledgeable and polite in her work.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Ordered using Grabfood. Treasure signature combo($27+) and the Boneless duck & chicken ($20+) with free chicken. Only the free chicken potion is real whole chicken. Everything else very little.
Always a pleasure to dine here, dishes are delicious and service impeccable.

35yrs of serving Hakka food.
What can go wrong?
Top rated!

#Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ
#ÁÆóÁõòÂ≠ê
Yummy and generous portion too!

This place was empty compared to Yishun branch. Yishun was pretty packed!

I tried their chicken nasi lemak before on the Yishun branch but here in Novena I tried the otah and hebie bun.

The otah was just okay, I didn't get the fish texture because it's too mushy. The the bun was soft enough but the amount and the taste of hebie compared to the size of the bun made this hebie bun became too salty.

Vote for the best chicken nasi lemak in town!
Didn‚Äôt really know what to order. May have ordered the wrong dishes. Service was great though.

Real authentic taste with modern twist. The rice of the signature Rice bowl is so damn good with right balance of truffle taste, furikake and pickled cucumber. I don‚Äôt eat beef but I had a taste of the rice, and it‚Äôs amazing. I‚Äôm sure the beef is vy nice too. The temaki, grilled hamachi and grilled assorted mushrooms with butter, are yummy too. Tbh I didn‚Äôt expect the simple mushroom to be this addictive. Hope to see more non beef choices on menu, provided they manage to up their manpower. Shortage of manpower happens at every industry at this time, sigh.
Usually will have queue at night (both weekday and weekend). Food is nice, although sometimes the waiting time for food served can be around 15-25mins.
Not bad! Can eat! Ordered the Black Pig Pork cutlet, meat is juicy and the breaded Panko batter is light. Price is reasonable. Will come back!

Second time visiting this outlet here at Jurong Point. It was a Sunday and needless to say, there‚Äôs quite a queue.. The ‚Äúwaiting area‚Äù was pretty warm and could do with some ventilation.

The waitress who attended to us was probably new as she had to went back and forth consulting her colleagues each time I ordered a different sushi on a different category. I would suggest to provide iPad on every table, like what many other establishments already are doing, so to convenience us consumers. Because fact is, she keyed in the wrong order for one of them, and it tasted awful ü§¢

I have to highlight the fact that the soft shell crab is a must-have given that it is actually crispy, and actually contains crab meat! I‚Äôm really surprised and regretted not going for another round..

All in all, the food was good and the price reasonable.
Good mutton briyani & pratas no doubt. Only thing is their tables are always oily and dirty. Wipe with a tissue and behold the color change yourself. Nevertheless I'll still come back for the food.

Ordered the Mee Soto Drumstick and Mee Rebus Chicken.

Not worth the hype at all. Super mediocre. Very little ingredients and the soup is unflavorful.

I've had so much better one out there..
Eat at xinghua at seletar mall. Their services is good and their food is delicious. There are a variety of food to choose from.

The experience with the staff was not the most pleasant and same goes for the food . Set menus came with chilli crab that only consisted of 1 small crab and 4 mantous even for a table of 10 people . The food was average and nothing to praise , for the shellfood like abalone , it was overcooked and super rubbery according to my family members . There is indeed a need for improvement in the cooking preparations and taste .
Good service. Food just OK.

Nice ambience after the lunch crowd has passed.

Loved the vibes.

Food is dismal though. The chicken pasta is very tasteless and the pumpkin soup is very watery and tasteless.

Coffee was fine.

Price is slightly high as considered for porridge,however they are located inside a shopping mall so prices are considered reasonable in this setting, the quality is good and youtiao is crispy. Props for creating dishes suitable for all ages.

Ordered food via the food court app and waited  7 minutes before the app said food is ready for collection. When went to collect, the lady had no idea what I ordered and had to tell her and waited another 10 minutes. All these tech is useless if your people are not trained to use them

The lady by the cashier was really rude and offered close to no help. The menu offered a wide variety of food which took me a while to glance through but I was not spared by her glares as she stood by the cashier waiting for my order. I feel that that if you are in the frintline of the shop mending the cashier, there should be a minimum standard to uphold. The food might be affordable and decently tasting but the attitude of the lady left me with a taste of disgust.

I would definitely not be visiting this place anytime soon.
Ok
You pay hawker centre prices for restaurant sized steaks. Highly recommend
Fun and fantasticüò¨üò¨
Very good teochew-thai cuisine...can come often.

As many have commented, the black bean sauce noodles are good. Price increased by a lot (set C from $46 to $53) before service charge, and this just happened this month I think. I saw some reviews had bad experiences with the aunties and that happened to me too. Place was 20% full and what‚Äôs the issue with us shifting to a bigger table when the small table was not enough to accommodate our food comfortably? It was Sat evening but still early at 6pm. When we left at around 7pm, there were still 2-3 empty big tables. It‚Äôs a turn off when these ppl can‚Äôt even display some proper service and had to argue with the customers over such petty stuff. That auntie was sarcastic too and said we requested to change the table a few times, that was due to her poor Eng and comprehension that the first table near to entrance had hot and cold air alternations whenever the front door is being opened and we wanted to shift inside to another table (also 4-seater which she rejected and insisted for us to move to a 2-seater). After sitting down it felt too small as the set consists of two bowls of noodles and a big plate. The neighboring table (4-seater) also had 2 customers seated there ordering either similar things or lesser. So why the fuss about the move in order to ‚Äúreserve‚Äù it for bigger group?
Friendly service, affordable prices. A great choice in town! :)
You get u paid for. Skip the Chu Toro. It will ruined u for life.

Famous #NasiLemak in Yishun. Chilli is sweet, and their #Begedil is made manually. Decent, but not the best. Pricing is affordable. Paid $6 for 2 chicken wings, 2 eggs, 1 hotdog, 1 fishcake, ikan bilis and peanuts.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Summary: For the price-to-quality and long wait, go somewhere else.

The good: The food was of decent quality and the shrimp chee cheong fun had quite a lot of prawns in it. The average price of each dish is about $3.50, which is par for the course at a dim sum experience.

The bad: Despite the price, it isn't a full dim sum experience never it isn't a restaurant, but charges the same price. The operations are messed up with a lot of inefficiencies, leading to the customer collecting their food in bits and pieces (you need to collect it yourself - again less than a dim restaurant experience, where they deliver to your table) and the wait can be very long, depending on the dish - I had to wait for about an hour for the freshly fried red bean pancake! By then I wasn't hungry and lost eating momentum - I would have rather they didn't offer it at all if I knew I had to wait that long.
enjoyed every single bit of it. it has been a few days yet i‚Äôm still drooling over the photos we took lmao
Good location. Drinks taste, plain water will be charge.
delicious food

The Mrs and I ordered an assortment of dishes such as the porridge, tofu bomb, egg tarts, siew mai etc. The Mrs raved immensely about the porridge and it shows as we dropped by earlier today around noonish and the porridge was already out of stock. Personally, among all the dishes I tried, the tofu bomb is the one I would come back for. The price and portion is reasonable. It obtains what seems like diced up pieces of prawn, possibly fish paste, chives and probably small pieces of chilli. It is flavourful with a hint of spiciness from the chilli inside. As it's deep fried, it's the usual moist but mostly from the oil it soaked up from the cooking process. Ordering system and waiting time was acceptable. We were able to figure it out without any assistance. We will definitely come back for more again!

Established more than 30 years, a very homely ambience, good food and reasonable price. Love their Saba fish and grilled squid. Children love the garlic fried rice and tempura udon. Please make a reservation to avoid disappointment.
Nice

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Place just converted to Thai Hot Pot recently.  Price is reasonable only if you have Safra member 20% discount. Soup base is better compared to previous Suki-Ya but limited choices of ingredients. Believed its Halal certified so no pork served. Service average due to insufficient manpower.
Very rude staffs! In times of pandemic like this, many F&B establishments needed support. But please bring the support to other establishment who value customers, definitely NOT Malaysia Chiak.
The sushi is just above acceptable. It's not fresh since it's meant to be merely fast food. If you're looking for sushi near NTU, I recommend going to Jurong Point for Genki or Sushi-Go.
Fatty boom boom have consistently great taste, fried rice king offer great fried rice you can ask for .. superb
taste is impeccable!!!! so yummy that the 1h+ queue is definitely worth it

food was good, but only if you are a student. Istg the prices here have skyrocketed since I last came here to eat. recommend the food 8/10 but if you come here make sure ure a student. if not the prices here are like 16.90 for a bowl of spaghetti. bit I must admit try the dessert pizza. picture of the student meals are below

This is an example of good food accompanied by excellent service. I have been to several Putien in Singapore but I have to give a shoutout to the outlet in Northpoint City. They deserve the Michelin 1 star. They pay attention to the details (e.g. when I was holding a cake, the staff proactively asked if I needed him to place it in the fridge) and were generally friendly, helpful and attentive to requests.
Really good job to all the staff in this outlet on 1 2 May 2021! üëèüèªüëèüèª

It's a wonderful place when you have a family of young and old. Drop off elderly at LRT pick up point which is just outside restaurant. Sufficient big round tables for families. Park at hdb multistorey carpark beside seletar mall if you find mall parking too long queue or expensive.

Food is great here. Tasty, adequate servings, good service. They cook fast too.

Currently having promo 9.90 for  soon hock so good news for fish lovers.

The Heng hua thin bee hoon and lor mee suits different ages. Lychee meat will satisfy the young without fail, the special yam cubes for the older folks.

Give it a try esp if you're sick and tired of weekend crowd everywhere.

The food is delicious and the portion is just right. Their service is good too especially Wendy Wong. She gives us good recommendation of their signature food and inform on the promotion offered in the restaurant. I would this place for all occasions.Had a fantastic lunch experience at Silk Road. The ambiance has changed and added to the lovely experience. Ms Wendy was excellent and recommended the lunch menu which was excellent
Look at the Mee Rebus !!! Ingredient so rich. And quite delicious as well. Come Ang Mo Kio Avenue 10 Blk 453A Choong Boon Market & Food Centre @ stall #01-01 Rahim Muslim Food. Try it up !!!

I ordered Chicken Nasi Briyani at midnight thru grab, upon opening the packet, the stale smell was too overwhelming.....and it was from the cabbage (vege), like how can you serve those kind of food. Already vomited and yucksss.....
Very nice. Easy on the stomach and wallet

There was a short queue for weekday lunch. Sambal belacan portion was big but tastes watered down, Sayur lodeh was the worst I've had because it's bland and watery. Sambal goreng was unimpressive as it was quite soggy. I was caught off by how much potato was in it which I felt was a cheap way to disguise as bean curd rather than an improvement to the dish. Beef Rendang was ok but we were hoping for more sauce since it's not the soft and moist kind. It's my first time here and heard good reviews about it but my friend said the macik retired already so quality dropped. Don't think I'll be back for nasi padang of this price. $15 for 2 of us.

Tanoke is such a gem! Beautiful cosy place with good food and even better service. Unpretentious and really lives up to the online reviews.

Nareeth, thank you for making our evening so enjoyable, and ensuring that we didn‚Äôt over order. You have such good knowledge of your products and a wonderful passion for your job. We really appreciate that. Cheers!
Friendly staff, foods are delicious and very affordable :) Nice ambience! Clean restaurant and YUMMY! üòä

Hi, I would like to commend the jack's place team at Jurong safra outlet for an excellent service provided during my dine. You really have a very impressive team of staff. We found a hair in one of our course meal - aglio olio ordered by my friend. whilst i ordered the chicken cutlet. But the team compensated with both our meals as they saw that there was a piece of chicken cutlet in the aglio olio. Thanks team for making our dining experience here an awesome one. Will definitely recommend coming here.

Like the dessert.
Friendly staffs
Really liked this place!! Good vibes and good food, had no complaints on the customer service too! Maybe jus a tad lil pricey but i would say for the taste, i would definitely come back for more.

Great place for lunch where they offer lunch sets with a drink for around $5-7 depending on what you get. The place itself would benefit from some sprucing up especially the toilet as it can be somewhat dirty at times. Apparently famous for the lobster porridge but I have yet to try.

Food sucks and totally disappointing.
Popiah fillings is cold .... Even turnip is cold.
Claypot bak kut teh served lukewarm only and at $6 no rice only have 2 slices of super thin frozen pork belly and 2 pieces of hard like rock frozen pork ribs with 2 tiny strip of fried beancurd nothing else!!!!!!! So different from the photo at stall.  Won't come again.

Food under average , can tasted the seafood not so fresh already. waited quite long for the food waiting . If can I will give with no star but for the Google setting I can't . Service also horrible the gal think Vietnam or Philippines ask her anything seems like no response . If not happy you can just stay home don't look like people owe you money . Spent money come eat but not value at all....

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content:
üëçnice üëåsuper Good customer service, indian full grilled chicken  indian style. tamilnadu restaurants.
Thank you so much KARTHIK

Haven‚Äôt eat the yakiniku for a bit while. Recently just found one near by, its on the AMK hub basement 1. The food is fresh especially the meats, and with patient young staffs give efficient and friendly service. I was satisfied, set food size a bit small for me especially for this price. This is probably only concern from me.

I personally like the chili squid, very spicy. The fragrance of nasi lemak rice add to the tasty meal together with veg. Laksa taste normal. They got wide variety of choice for side dish to eat with plain rice or nasi lemak rice.

Just visited today @ 7 May 16 (7pm-9pm). Foods is good.

Service is disappointed on the last part during bill payment. They have counted wrongly for my bill.

When I seek clarification on the bill. The lady staff insisted the bill is right even we pointed out the mistake.

No choice we have to ask the manager who taken our order to verify. We are right n correct.

The lady stuff show No sense of remorsefulness, No apologize and No smile.

Just pass back us the corrected amount of Bill and walk away. Just like pass money to begger.

Totally disappointed.

Very unhappy customer
Ordered the set for 3 (although there's 4 of us) with soup, Samsui chicken, fried rice, potato leaves in sambal, tofu and dessert. Great meal at reasonable price.
Delicious Thai cuisine and efficient service on the whole. The seafood clear Tom yum soup was appetizing & not too spicy. Prawn cake taste nice.  Was a lovely dining experience.

This traditional handmade fish ball noodle stall from Malaysia was indeed delicious. Fishball and Fishcake were really ‚ÄúQ Q‚Äù and the noodles with pork lard tasted Malaysian style. This stall will be my ‚Äúgo to place‚Äù now for my kway teow soup or mee pok. However, expect long queue and only open from 8am to 12pm only daily and closed on Monday. And the best part is, the uncle and auntie are very friendly and nice. They were very patient with your orders.

Ordered their set dinner for 5 pax. The first half of the dishes are nice. However, the last 3 dishes were overly salty, the veg, the brocoli and the noodle with duck. All five of us found it too salty. We paid closed to $500, for this price, there are much better restaurant out there. Service is above average.

Really enjoy the food here. My family, especially my oldest son, loves the xiao long bao. I myself prefer the black vinegar chilli wontons. Price is steep, and waiting time can be long on some days, but my family enjoys every meal we've been there. Helps that we live within walking distance too.
Ordered chee cheong fun thru grab delivery. No sauce was given. How to eat!!??

Second time here. Service is always slow and bad despite an empty restaurant. 45 min of waiting.

All the staffs just stay group around chatting without following up on your orders.

Food is tasty.

Pls get them to work on service level.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Food quality varies according to the chef's mood I guess- some days are not too bad, other days are not as great. Also, it didn't really help that the customer service was quite bad. Made a takeaway order and waited half an hour. When asked staff politely approx how long more, she cannot seemed to bother to help check on order. Honestly, there are definitely better zichar places to visit that offers better food and much better customer service experience.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Marinated meat is shiok! Air con environment! Get ready to smell like bbq!
Pet friendly cafe in a quiet neighborhood. Quality of food is better than expected but selection range not wide- wish they have more desserts choices~

Hou sek!
Congee lover here. This is quite tasty. Steep price for congee though.. i would expect slightly more with that price but okay.. craving satisfied.

DON'T GO! I ORDERED FOOD AND IT TOOK MORE THAN AN HOUR TO COME.
SUPER SUPER BAD SERVICE, IGNORANT STAFF, RUDE BEHAVIOR.

A COMPLETE NO GO! BEWARE (Yeah you heard it right! BEWARE)
My go-to place to satisfy all my cravings for Japanese cuisine! I like how I could conveniently make my order by scanning the QR code printed on the table also there's also free Wi-Fi provided.

Since 20 over years till now the Beef Rendang still remains authentic! Every pkt bought sure must add additional Rendang. Sambal Balado is one of the best since I don't like too much Sambal Belacan. Nenek still working and clearing the plates, at this age!

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: I'm disappointed with my lunch at Aston in tao payoh safra. Is cold when they serve the steak. Is so hard. After hv the food there came home hv diarrhoea. This is going to be my last time going there.
It really bad. The soup is not rich, creamy and salty. It just bad. Super bad. Cant finish
Very delicious foods I like their xiaolongbao, dumplings, pancakes and hot n sour soup!
Nice place with nice food
Authentic Thai food. Good atmosphere. Spice kick is good. Thai ice tea is one of the best I've tried.

We tried Maki-san from the Junction 8 store last year and it was better. We ordered Grab delivery from this store in the recent weeks and it seems that either the quality has dropped, or this store does not have the same standards as the Junction 8 store:

1) the rice was not up to standards and mushy.
2) the fried items were so hard that they might be leftovers from the previous day, and they just heated it up either by re-frying or using the microwave.
3) some of the non-fried food items might have gone slightly bad (because there is a smell).

We have forgotten to leave a review on Grab though.

Also, do note that the amount might be smaller than you expect.

Standard fast food. Part of the Secret Society thats keeping LJS alive. Haha.
Yum yum.

Service kinda mixed up sometime
The venue is big and spacious. The staffs working on that day have been attentive and responsive to our table requests. The food was great too. Awesome experience for our family that day.

As a regular customer of Ichiban Sushi, I tried many different combinations, no matter sushi, tampura, udon, ramen, sashimi, or the beef, pork, chicken, Ichiban Sushi never disappointed me.
The Garlic Chicken Wazen is very popular, and YES! you can't miss it.
Salmon Belly Mentai Yaki is also recommended, I ordered it almost every time!
Some dessert like a Motcha ice cream is a perfect treat after the meal.
Remember to gain your points on their customer loyalty card, to exchange some free items.

When you crave for something and it‚Äôs just around the corner.üòãüå∏Have you ever visited The Larder? If not yet, then it‚Äôs time for you to explore..3-5 minutes walk from Toa Payoh Mrt,you gonna love the place,the food are amazing,the ambiance is cozy. I really love to come here and bring my friends to try every dish they have. Just so love to spend time with friends here and having a brunch. The price are affordable with easy access of their menu. Btw they are using QR menu as well,it is fast and easy to order. Highly Recommended.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Our first visit was fine, but there are limited food choices and staff issue.

However we still decided to come again, only for the Sukiyaki soup base, but we were informed that it is only a promotional item.

Please bring it back. It is so difficult to find a halal hotpot restaurant which serves Sukiyaki soup base ( because it mainly uses wine ).

Thank you

Service was great.
Noise level was not. Private room partitions are those flimsy Chinese screens which are not floor to ceiling and neither are they sound proof.

Food was disappointing for the price we paid. Food lacks the ‚Äòomph‚Äô factor. I would describe them as flat, bland and/ or spicy. As a local, you can get way better food at this price in a good Chinese restaurant, with good sound proofing. Most of the dishes we ordered are on the recommendations list. Imagine if we ordered the non recommended ones.

The best dish was the starter, Chilled Organic Vine-ripened Tomatoes.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
The best mookata in town .Meat and seafood amd vegetables is fresh.Highly recommend the marinated pork belly and garlic pork/chicken, its tasty .The spicy chilli sauce the best!!üëçüèª
Reasonable price and friendly staff. Always crowded and quite long wait but its worth it!! Recommended !!

Been here at least 5 times. Service is below the industry standard. Waited 1 hour for my food. Poor communication between servers and kitchen staff. Staff appear busy but do nothing.  Ask for wasabi but they never return. Not interested in serving you or taking your order unless you call them. Overall a very lousy experience and I suspect its poor management at this outlet!
My go to fix for Penang prawn noodles! I don't know how they did it but it taste better than 888 ones in Penang. I did not try their lor mee although I had been ther for like 10 times. Haha.
Great food and very attentive staff! There were a few fusion Chinese dishes like the truffle chicken which we enjoyed.The tomato starter was unique!
1 norm mee robus - nice savoury sauce and mee soto special with huge drumstick and bagedel... soto sauce is not my favour but its norm. Chilli is power. Worth the trip

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Delicious nasi padang, very affordable, service good!
Wonderful ambience for a small gathering.  Good food served at Jubilee Garden Restaurant.  Very friendly environment plus cheerful staff to enhance our meal at this location.
Food is really tasty, very authentic thai food. Ladyboss is also very friendly.
super disappointed... i wont come agian
