restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Great taste and reasonably priced. They offer free home delivery for orders above $60

Very friendly staff who‚Äôs accommodating to our requests. Dinner with 24 pax and food was great. They even allowed us to bring our own cake with no extra charge; provided us with plates & utensils for cake cutting too.

Service was bad.. Shortage of staff..
here noone wants to serve us.. Totally zero lakc of comm.. Order took too long to come..

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Can't go wrong having your fix of Chinese cuisine at Crystal Jafe

Decent prices, great atmosphere, an extensive menu, and food that does not disappoint. Be prepared to queue for a while (~15min in my experience), and it is certainly worth the short wait. Heard that their fish and chips is really good, but I haven't tried it yet. Will certainly try it in future.

This place is super underrated !!!
The food here was so good that we ordered another round of the same dishes ! If you're looking for the classic Hakka Abacus (ÁÆóÁõòÂ≠ê), look no further ! They made it really fragrant and soft in texture. The dishes in my images are definitely fail safe. Order them to try!
Didn't have high expectations as I hadn't heard of it before. Ordered as takeaway and the flavours and quality blew me away!   You can tell it's cooked from the heart. One of my top 2 nasi padang.

Rice used not very good quality, when you have char siew sauce it doesn't taste good. The noodles were better.

Shrimp dumpling is huge, $1 each. Although lots of meat with a small whole shrimp in it, I would describe it as very rough execution, which is a menu item you can skip.

With noodle and rice charged at $5.50, which is good court pricing, I would not say it was value for money. Food good enough to satisfy your hunger or crave for roast meat, but not a place to visit due to quality/value of meal.
Really love this place for steamboat! Really recommend it ! Products are so fresh and clean! The pork broth is really good as well!

I‚Äôm surprised that there‚Äôs just 1 review done for this food business. Since COVID-19 CB, my family have ordered several times (if not weekly) for their tasty and affordable meal delivery. We were initially attracted to the fair pricing (think $5 for a Chicken Chop with delicious Brown Sauce, and 2 well portioned sides well packed in divider tray). Then there‚Äôs no turning back... we start trying all kinds of Japanese & Western food selection, and almost all satisfied. And for the 1 Sushi Tray which we commented that the rice texture is too hard from excessive pressure, this flaw is corrected immediately on next order. Very impressive business owner, who take feedback seriously. This is also the reason why I felt compelled to leave this positive review. They deserve to do better and survive current difficult wave. By saying that, I‚Äôm also helping those who order food deliveries on frequent basis. Their pricing is Very Affordable!! Especially if you live around their stall @ Koufu NYP. I reside in Sengkang and enjoys special discounted delivery fee at just $3 when I order in for my family of 4. Imagine $5 x 4 meals, add $3 for transport and that is just $23 nett for a good dinner delivered to doorstep.

Finally, I would like to recommend our family‚Äôs favourites: Chicken Chop with Brown Sauce ($5), Hawaiian Chicken Chop ($6), Mexican Chicken Chop ($6), Mashed Potato that are served with the mains, Oyako-don ($5) and the 8-piece Sushi Tray ($7).
I like the bee hoon here.
Always one of our fav places to eat roasted meats and clay pot rice. Servers have always been friendly and chitchat with our lil girl too. Very homely place ÔºÅ

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
Blk 127, 128 n 124 form a triangle of good food n activity.

At 127 is the popular local mkt,
the fresh fish stalls looked clean n lively, plenty of vegetables n a row of friendly clothes stalls too.  Food Centre on upper level (has Teochew handmade pau stall).  Plant for sale grd level corner is gd value.
At 128 is Niche Cafe, hair salon n sundry shops for housewares n cute hair accessories.  Far corner of this block is coffeeshop with very good Roast Meat rice stall.

At 124 is good value Hakka Yong Tau hu n a seafood restaurant in airy coffeeshop. For amusement, there's Japan Home store.  Blk facing 124 has good reflexology at Healing Hands.
Because the prata very nice n the place so simple üòéüòâ

A very neat & clean chic air con Chinese restaurant. To be fair, for $6/- a small black hot clay pot of Lao Hero Laksa is graded satisfactory. The sliced fish cakes were not fresh and only 2 medium size prawns. Much improvement needed on the laksa.

Really delicious and cheap Malaysian food right here in Singapore. The KL hokkien Mee, Char Kway Teow and claypot are must-trys. If you are into rojak, give it a go as well. The ambience and decor makes you feel like you are in Malaysia. But expect long queues and you may have to stand around for a while before getting a seat.

The menu here is quite extensive with lots of variants and the flagship Butashoga is a pretty good at such a low price-point. Sadly, the other ramen we tried was a flop and the extra sides we had are pretty run-of-the-mill fried food. But nonetheless, at the rate they ‚ÄúKanzen‚Äù, we are sure to be back again to try their other ramen.

Jack's Place is a restaurant that many locals would be familiar with. It provides good value for money lunch sets which has me returning every now and then. Especially like the potato with sour cream, chives and bacon bits. Service at this outlet is friendly and prompt. Will be returning here to get my fix
Nice ambient but I won't be back for the food..

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Restaurant is very clean and food is good.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
The staff were very helpful and friendly!
Food were of good standard too!

Dine in today and the food taste much better than takeaway. Their Chee Cheong Fun is the signature dish, you can have it many ways, dry, soy sauce, curry, plain and many more. The rice roll is soft and taste better either way. I think that makes their speciality as their Hor Fun also have the same texture. Their noodles also not bad. Although prices are slightly higher than food court, but I think their speciality makes them worth a try if you craving for Malaysian tasted food and dining ambience Is very comfortable with aircon. Last but not least, their Ipoh coffee is thick and creamy too.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Food and service is really good. All the servers are very attentiveness will come back again
Uncle Sim moved from Blk 137 Potong Pasir Ave 3. Both the lontong and mee siam are tasty although I like the lontong more.

It's nice to have another Sushi Train option. Every one has their own specialties and reason to patronize. For Sushi Go I like the varieties of Sashimi they offer. There are slightly more premium items as compare to others. Hopefully there will be more branches soon.
First time trying and will be the last. Cashier is extremely rude. Have not come across such service for a long time in Singapore. Spoils my dinner.
Found Malaysia delicacies I would recommend. I like the curry with pork skin! Serve with the ice coffee it‚Äôs the best match. Yummy!

Quite overpriced for a school establishment. Quality does not justify the price.

Edit: All the 5-star reviews appearing all within a span of a few hours last week just after the few 1 star reviews seems abit sus. Suspect these be fake/employee accounts manipulating the review score - Polarising reviews of 5stars vs 1 stars abit of a give away. (I hope not, but I'll give the benefit of the doubt here). For the record I ate their chicken tikka and it wasn't great - I dont know what those people are talking about. Unless there was a significant improvement over such as short time. No hard feelings but I sincerely hope that the owners take a hard look at their business model and really consider the criticism of the lower reviews. You guys just opened, there is still time to improve things. It'll be a waste of such potential especially with a different dining concept. All the best!

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Almost perfect Mookata experience üòÅ
Love the peking duck, will definitely visit with my friends again!
Loved the Assam curry! The second discovery was the kailan 2 ways. The fried kailan leaves were shiok! Overall a very satisfying meal

Yummy... I love the set food... so good. Then finish off with hot coffee...
I had a good time with my family.
The place was clean..
Spring Chicken Set and Fish n Chips are good.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Nothing fancy. Just your regular neighbour dim sum. Not bad either.

Zichar style food at zichar pricing with aircond. Very fast service, pleasant servers. Able to call in advance to make reservations.

Food quality wise (perhaps it‚Äôs the dishes that I ordered), I don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs exceptional. Some dishes were tad too salty, some lack the final
Oomph.

Perhaps I‚Äôll come back to try the curry fish head that everyone is raving about.

packed my nasi padang for lunch...sufficient in variety ..veg ..seafood and meats...good sambal and great rendang .....a balanced pricing ...
can also eat there ..  a coffee shop setting ...üëç
Ordered tiger prawn n mushroom spaghetti , but given frozen small little prawn . DO NOT WRITE IN MENU TIGER PRAWN

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: This store is usually good but today was disappointing. Hope this is not the usual standard. The nuts/ikan bills tasted a little stale. Chicken wing batter is not like before (not sure if recipe changed). Sambal is still good Thank goodness. If only the egg doesn't have a "MacDonald shape" and fried more naturally .. Anyway always has been a good store to me so hope today is not the new standard going forward.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content:
Ordered the double egg cheese prata and it came very fast seems like pre cooked and totally no cheese taste and very soggy.
Ask the chef he claimed the cheese is grated into it I really doubt so cause I cannot taste any cheese at all.

Staffs were rude!!!!!!! Ordered watermelon juice and took 45 mins to come after we ate all the food
Worst experience when we were damn hungry

Delicious don with smell of barbecue. The sliced  pork has little bits of bone, so needs to be careful for small children. Online ordering is not recommended as it only accepts PayPal. Perhaps they could upgrade to accept other modes of payment for online ordering. So it‚Äôs best to order from the counter. They accept PayNow, NETS and cash at the counter.

The food was rather tasty. Personally I liked the water chestnut fritters, crab tang hoon ($60/kg during this Chinese New Year period - you can call and ask about the crab price before going down), and definitely the yam dessert!
Above average local restaurant - worth a visit anytime.
The rice is too hard and sticky! Not sure if it's overcook or undercook! Paid near $20 dollars get disastrous food. Please take note of the QC~

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Wow I have never came across this restaurant even though I have walked past it without noticing it so many times until a Korean friend recommended me this restaurant.
I am usually a Korean cuisine person and not so much on Korean-Chinese but this restaurant totally proofed me wrong that Korean-Chinese can be very good too!
I walked in it just felt so Korean I believe there were a lot of Koreans dining there. I was brought into the corner room where the other 2 tables were also Koreans. I was thinking to myself this place must be good and authentic!
Went with my gut feeling to pick a set and added a Kimchi pancake. Food was served pretty promptly and smelled good.
The dumplings was hot and crispy, very enjoyable. Then came the kimchi pancake and the jajiangmyeon. Am pretty surprised the portion was rather generous thank God we got enough people to finish everything.
Jajiangmyeon is definitely the best I have eaten in Singapore, the sauce is so good and not salty at all. 2 of us shared the jajiangmyeon and we were quite full already didn't really we still had the Jjamppong. Soup was not really spicy and it was very delicious. Didn't know why after the meal my lips felt like it was burning. Forgot about the main star of the meal which I thought was the sweet and sour pork. Wow the sauce is so good, so mild but has the essential flavours and taste.
Really enjoyable meal here definitely will make it to the often visit list!

Slow service. Served all dishes and worse, served the fried rice last. They fried the rice one shot with other's orders. Which was unacceptable. And so, we have to wait too long despite the fact that we ordered first. The xiao long bao crabmeat smell tested not fresh and have many bones in it. Not juicy. Noodle portion was little. Fried rice tasted like no salt fried rice meant for kids. Dissapointed as hell. Just the name is big, but food not nice.

Yummy prawn noodle soup and lor mee!! The uncle at the stall was also very friendly and recommended we try the original prawn noodle and lor mee (though I wanted to try the yuan yang lor mee - with prawn noodle soup mixed in - which would have me $1 more). I'm glad I heeded his advice.

The lor mee was tasty and the prawn noodle broth rich in flavor.

It's only 4 stars cos it's a hawker centre
Surprisingly good. Loved the eggplant and salted mushroom.

Recently the restaurant was renovated. The good aspect is that this restaurant is open 24 hours
Food quality is good. They have verity of food which includes Indian, Malay, Chinese, Thai and western.
The owner and management are Muslim and food is halal but they don't have singapore halal certificate as they didn't apply for.
Great tasting home cooked style in both vegetarian and non-vegetarian dishes. Food cooked without the use of MSG to get the great authentic Indian food taste.
Food and service was good. Serving was fast and the cendol was very nice..

First and last vist here for sure ! The service is atrocious, called 3 different staffs (guy with green hair, old aunty with short hair, prc lady with pony tail) at different intervals to check on my seafood noodles but none of them bothered to respond, just simply brushed me aside. We waited for almost 40 mins and my noodles is not served still. I now asked the 5th staff whom checked with the tall dark colored skin non chinese looking lady at cashier then informed us its coming. After waited for another 5 mins, the noodles just never arrived ! I was visibly super upset and proceeded to cancel order. The taste of their XLB is nothing spectacular, you are better off with DTF or Daxi @ Velocity which served better dumplings. Foods are NOT authentic Hokkien, nor authentic Putien, neither are they authentic Peranakan ! They have lost their identity, as rojak as Singapore. You have a better deal eating at real Putien franchised restaurants @ Ion, Vivo, Kitchener Rd. The taste of their food, and presentation is just about another wannabe Pu Tian, you dont even wanna see how they pack your food if you order via grab/panda, really dont even talk about service which is way below sub-par. You are definitely happier dining @ Hans or Mun Zuk porridge next door ! Spent your $$$ there at your own risk !
Shanghai soup buns. Steamed to perfection with crispy base. Bite in for the hot and flavorful meat juice! Super recommend, come early to beat the long queue. üëçüèª

Great place and atmosphere!!! Price is definitely worth it, food is awesome, fresh and hot and the staff and boss are super friendly. Very proactively served us the fried food, ice cream, fruits and just a very good experience that I would highly highly recommend to everyone!!! Super duper worth it so must come and visit!! Good price, good food, good people.
Great atmosphere, food and staff. Been here a couple of times and always a good experience.
The guys is very rude  in taking order.. wearing red shirt i order on 27/11/20.
One Of My Favorite Places To Visit When I Have e Sudden Crave For Western Cuisines... üòã Their Almost Everything In List Are Cheap & Good!!
Awesome service and sweet crew who gifted my daddy longevity peaches for his birthday. They even made it fresh cos they ran out of it. Thank you!!!

Usually come here for porridge. But thought i try their tim sum. Variety is not wide, but quality is good. I had pork ribs. The portion is generous n taste is delicious üòã.  Had the spring roll; crisp n fresh. They have a new item, if you like otah n in mood for the fusion of it, come try their cheese otah. Taste of otah remains with added chewy cheese. üëç
Very slow service. 30min wait for prata.
Nice food, the usual BTK experience. It was quite crowded on a weekday lunch hour. Be sure to arrive early.
Nice and unique food but best of all they played my favourite Kit Chan songs in the background making the restaurant even more classy!
Excellent food and service

Went Yishun Putien during Mid Autumn festival. ÈùôÈõ™ (staff of Putien) was a great host and was very patience with us throughout the whole experience.

Nothing expected from them but they went extra miles to ensure we are well attended. Definitely a great place to visit again.
Great food, good service, reasonably priced! Will be back

Had the kuey teow, chendol, and popiah.
Forgot to take the photo of the kuey teow.

The chendol was pretty authentic tasting. Similar to the one i had in penang. However, the ingredients are found to be lacking in quantity. The green jello and the red beans were very much missing and only had a very small quantity.

The char kuey teow was not bad. Except it was missing a key ingredient namely the lap cheong. Chinese sausage. Other than that, 70% alike.

The popiah was decent. Not fantastic but okay.

Not sure why we have to keep our own plates here since it's more a restaurant than a hawker centre.

Love the food here..The Southern and Northern Indian food is super gud..You definitely have to try their Satti Soru here and also the Fish Head Curry..Overall everything is good here the food n drinks too..Staffs are super friendly too

Walked past this restaurant few weeks ago and saw many people enjoying their steam boat with ‚Äúimperial design‚Äù steamboats. Finally booked the restaurant for the family dinner. We enjoyed the steamboat‚Ä¶ super fresh fish and soup was flavorful and not salty.

I love the braised duck‚Ä¶ meat was super soft and simply delicious.

Making a reservation was a bit of a mess‚Ä¶ they used WhatsApp but when we arrived, they didn‚Äôt capture the reservation. So call the restaurant to be sure. Try to get a seat at the extension area of the restaurant where it is much cooler.
Service was excellent and more than make up for the quality of the food. Food was not too bad but definitely has room for improvement.

Food were decently nice. Ambience like a typical Chinese restaurant. Prices soso, but cheap if presented the ite alumni card.

We had my dad birthday dinner at first culinary.  Had notably memorable kl style char siew, Peking duck (duck from Ireland). The rest were normal chinese restaurant food. No complaints.

Went on a weekday evening. Not much crowd.

If travel by public transport, not the most easy. Have to take bus to reach to destination.

Yesterday, my family and I went to your restaurant for lunch. The food and ambience were nice. The Peking Duck is a must-try. I like the way they cut out the meat and serve it. It's so different from other restaurants as I can eat the best part of the duck meat. The service crew are friendly, especially Daphne. She is very good, cheerful, proactive and experienced. She explains my questions in detail, and I like the photos that she took for us. The shots and angles are so nice. Dong Dong is very helpful too. All my requests are well attended to. I would like to compliment their service. The only thing to take note of is that they serve the dishes super fast, so you must not order all at once, as the table is unable to accommodate all the dishes at once. This makes us a bit too rushed to finish the dishes instead of slowly tasting the food.

Thai food is known for being one of the popular food in Singapore. There are a bunch of Thai restaurants in here, but if you want to have some of the best Thai food available in Singapore, then you should go to Super Thai By Soi Aroy. The food is great and the price is reasonable. I highly recommend this place to anyone who wants to try out some authentic Thai food!

üëçüèΩ Grilled Pork Cheeks - must order! Nicely torched and tenderness of the meat.

üëçüèΩ Premium Tom Yum Soup

üëçüèΩ Red Ruby - must order! Sweetness is just nice and the awesome taste of the milk. Most delicious red ruby dessert ever!

üëçüèΩAurora Cooler - must order! Very special nice drink. Butterfly pea flower tea with lime juice. The pea flower gives a very fragrant taste to the drink unlike normal lime juice.

Follow reviewikr on Facebook and Instagram for more reviews.

Was at their Mt Alvernia branch for lunch today. Ordered their Tori Teriyaki Bento. The meat was uncooked and still red. They took it back to recook the meat and placed it back to onto the bento. Half way thru eating found a piece of plastic inside. It looks like a handplaster but they claimed it is just a plastic wrap for their seaweed that they accidentally dropped into the bento!! What a lousy restuarant with poor hygeine standard. Will never go back!

We booked the private area dining to host guests on Tuesday. The halal set meal came more than an hour late. The restaurant was not apologetic and did not inform us at all until we checked with the kitchen. We booked the private area dining for Thursday but we wanted to postpone it one day before due to medical concerns. The restaurant did not allow postponement, did not propose alternative solution and was not willing to negotiate at all about the whole situation. There was completely no flexibility and no compassion. We were told that we will be charged regardless and the food will be served. Fine. We went for the lunch and are now eating in the restaurant. There is a fly in my glass as I am writing this review now.

Great service and ambience. The duck and the beef tenderloin was very nice. I thought the enoki was something different, like a spiced snack which is q nice. The mee sua is also beautiful. Not a fan of the lion mane mushroom and avocado even though it was recommended.
Tasty food that is a highlight of the vicinity

I love this place! I have been patronising them from 2010 when they were in Northpoint shopping mall Kopitiam. They have been quite consistent with their food quality. Their briyani rice fragrant and the gravies flavour bomb, i Favour the boneless mutton briyani with fish cutlet. Yum. my husband likes their chicken briyani. I would be happy if they can do island wide delivery. It‚Äôs troublesome to order now from them.

Hidden gem on the second floor of Tanjong Pagar Plaza. I wouldn‚Äôt have known of this place if it weren‚Äôt for a friend‚Äôs recommendation. Pork Chop Egg Fried Rice ($8) is great! Rice is fluffy and separated, pork chop is just nice, and chili is the real hero. Will definitely come again to try the other stuff!

Has a variety of Malaysian food catered to the Singaporean taste. Char Kwey Teow, Pork noodle, Fried carrot cake, Nasi Lemak, Cendol, Clay Pot Rice, Chicken/Pork cutlet rice, etc. Seating is limited & social distancing applies. If you forgot to comply, the cleaners here will nag you about it so pay attention.

Very satisfying meal. Not disappointed after multiple visits. Always up to expectation. Very good to satisfy cravings for Thai food in the neighborhood. The atmosphere was very cozy and comfortable. Thailand's standards, make me feel like I‚Äôm in Bangkok. Boss Kathon very smiley and friendly person who always makes happy to each customer. TKS

I frequently patronise EN Sakaba in Tanjong Pagar as it‚Äôs near my office so decided to order delivery through oddle. Was disappointed that the wagyu stamina Don was full of veggies, mushroom, and NOT beef. The buta don pork is tough. Only saving grace is the egg and edamame. Also, the delivery guy was late (supposed to be 6-6.30 but he only came at 6.40, somemore Jem isn‚Äôt very far from choa chu kang) üò¢

Restaurant has been around for years but revamped menu recently serving dishes fr  Lokkee. It‚Äôs lokkee pricing too . The fire cracker chicken is $30. New dishes has up pricing to be on the steep side . It‚Äôs chicken bits fried in salt , dried Chili , ginger, spring onions , Sichuan peppers.  The yellow yolk look alike is actually mango sauce .

Special call out to the barramundi fillet atop bed of vege and toufu in a collagen soup base .
Fish fillet was thick, fresh , $88 can feed 4 to 6 pax .

Xiao long Bao was till good , the dumplings in Chili oil was nice too .
Big portion for the price. Value for money. Drink is nice also. Would come back again

Go there 10 MTH ago , overall the taste quite ok..today take away few dish..the laksa only taste sweet , The salted egg squid very expensive not worth anymore.. won't go again. For those like Penang food can try (Island Penang kitchen)
Best Thai Food in SG. Better than many we have tried! Full 5 stars for this fantastic restaurant. Right smack in a coffee shop! Price reasonably at 10 per pax or less.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: right amount of spicyness. feels like im in BKK streets

It's a pathetic experience with management over hear. We ordered food and waited for almost 45 minutes, we clearly could see that the guy who was serving food was giving orders to those who came after us. When we asked for food management misbehaved its not that he is giving food for free, we are paying for food then he is providing his services, clearly doesn't know how to do business.

Visit here if you want to see mismanagement and get misbehaved.

Good luck if you are eating here.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content:
It was very good with the right chef, I would give 5/5. Fresh, with sweet flakes. But with the wrong chef, it tasted bland and rancid. Oh yes, the fish stinks my entire room like trash (don't believe, buy it and try)
Now it's way worse. The sushis lack fish eggs and ingredients. Take a look at the photo! it's the most pathetic thing for your money. Doesn't taste good either, lacks ingredients. It been going on for the past 4 purchases.
Sadly I have stopped buying from last week.
Hidden gem in the Potong Pasir neighbourhood. Food and drinks are tasty and priced affordably. Service from the owner Kevin is the highlight and will definitely be back regularly.

Had tried a few times ever since I chance upon this makan place. They have recently come up with a new dish "Tom Yam Pasta" and it's delicious. The chicken satay is absolutely tasty and tender, satay sauce is perfect. Not forgetting the Root Beer float üç∫ , which is my all times favourite drink. The staffs are nice and friendly, it makes you relax and your meals enjoyable.
Affordable meals and tasty lor mee
We have the pleasure of Charles serving us this evening. He was very attentive to our needs. Haven't had such good service in a long long time. Thank you very much! üôè

Authentic, delicious Thai food

Pad thai
Egg wrap with seafood in tomato sauce
Kai lan
Basil chicken
Clear tom yum soup

All are good üëç
Prompt service with friendly staff! Ingredients are very fresh too with quite substantial portion.
The chef looks young, but their black pepper Sirloin steak at medium rare is really good. Nice cut and cook well to our liking. Will come back for other food items.  Keep up the good food.

Would like to give commendation on your staff called hockseng and Xavier Seah on a Saturday night dinner, 3rd April 2021. They recommended us with good suggestions and all were good and delicious. Food also came on time and staff were really courteous and friendly always checking on us whether the food is good and whether all food has arrived. Definitely looking forward to have dinner with my family here again. :)

Amazing cloud concept chicken so you can get food from various estabs all in one place! There‚Äôs Lerk Thai, Pho Street, newly opened King of Fried Rice, Niigata, Hill Street Coffee Shop and Hong Kong Sheng Kee Dessert. Air conditioned waiting area makes the long wait bearable in the tropical summer heat. You also collect your orders in a contactless manner. Great concept and great first encounter with a cloud kitchen!

Food is nice and delicious, staffs are friendly.
But they took my orders wrong :(

A set meal of Grilled Barramundi with Hollandaise Sauce, Cream of Shiitake Mushroom and Mango Mousse Sliced Cake with Earl Grey Tea fills the hungry belly üòã
If you're a small eater, please bring your family to savor the delicious western meal.
Love this place. Super well cooked food and super sweet couple. Love the pad thai!
Food is quite good but service can be further improved. Price is very reasonable but the waiting time can be very long.
Best nasi Lemak in Jurong. Better than the one at Boon Lay shopping center. Beware of Long queue but worth the queue.
If u like savoury and spicy, look no further.
Never will complain about the chicken. The meat is tender. Generally good service and good food. Only need to take note of side dish price before you order. Some side dish could be over price!!
Nice place to have a good meal.  The price is ok.  There have some nice meals there.

Ordered the steamboat - $35.
Fish is extremely fresh, soup is slightly bland but gets sweeter as it simmers with the vegetables. Has yam, tofu, cabbage in the soup as well.

Beef hor fun is great, been here 3 times already and ordered each time. Quality of the dish may vary, not as nice when it‚Äôs crowded but it‚Äôs very good when it‚Äôs less crowded.

Ok.. this is decent.. not stellar.. it's not a destination for cze char (for our family) .. great if it's downstairs your apartment. Contrary to some other comments - we enjoyed the ÊãõÁâå beehoon the most, pork ribs, prawns, eggs, and vege were all average.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: It was very bad experience we have several tea and coffee and other stuffs but owner refuse give 1 tissue paper
Prata with sambal sardine. Nice
Nice to have freshly baked pasta and not expensive and portion was reasonable with the price compare to outside.

Pricey due to its small portions, menu is also very very limited (so tried most of the dishes). Their best dish was the fried spring roll which brought out the sweetness of the cabbage and was served piping hot and crispy. One wrong order was we wanted stirfry wild yam but came egg with chives which was nice. Not a fan of the mei Cai kou rou ( the taste and pork abit dry) but the lotus bun had very fine texture. Noodles texture was good, taste of the chicken one is better than the pork as the 2nd was abit bland. The braised beef noodle broth is very tomataey.The pan fried bao bottom was overdone so was too hard but filling was good. Wantons are just ok. The stir fry french beans looked so pathetic with small portions and just pure bean. XLB is not too good, felt that the wrapper was too chewy and the filling too little to taste. Overall was disappointing meal and money could have been better spent on zichar.

We had these and then some!

10/10 would return!

Awesome service and ambience as well!
Great array of selection for sake lovers too!

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: I order tea and coke float the boss charge me $3. But the staff bring  the drink tea and normal coke and I asked where is my coke float. Then the boss came to me you want the coke float need to paid other $3. And he showed me the recipe is $4.50 why I need to paid other $3 suppose I just paid $1.50 more for the coke float. But the boss said no need other $3. I asked him explain why I need to paid other $3 and your shop coke float how much the coke float. He cannot a answer my question.

Just putting an honest review here.
Decent food (abit salty for me) decent price.

The stall owner is friendly and nice but really need to work something out to speed up the orders if you don‚Äôt want to lose customers.
Pratas are freshly made. Teh halia is good.
Simply yummy
If you like homed cooked style and simple dishes. Don't expect anything fancy, usually morning half of the day

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: First time i tried this and this is probably the most worth it sushi I‚Äôve ever tried in Singapore. It taste better than normal sushi you buy at convenience store, cheaper price, and has more variety. I will come back for sure to try the bowl.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Always delightful experience! Service staff is so friendly and food is always on point!

Ordered a Half Spring Chicken Set which came with two side dishes of your choice.

Reasonably priced at $5.90 however the Spring Chicken is too over fried as such it is dried and tough.

Sides dishes are acceptable.

Waiting time can be from 20mins onwards during peak hours.
Nice burger

Rarely find char siew to be soft and juicy nowadays, all too lean and healthy, surprisingly good one from ÂõõÁúº‰ªî.
ÁÉßËÇâ also good, skin is crispy but doesn‚Äôt stick between teeth, good roast.
However sauce is too sweet for me.
Ordered the grilled chicken briyani and added mutton. Serving as large enough for two adults. The food is good and even better than some briyani restaurants.

Decent choice for Indian food in the west part of Singapore
Courteous staff..
Good ambience..
Must try chicken lollipop, pepper chicken, malai kebab, masala kulcha
either cash or grabpay. very very inconvenient. only 4 narrow seats. price keeps increasing. forget it.
Kway teow goreng is tasteless and there is no sign of mince meat.

For 2 cup of tea and 4 prata (2 eggs and 2 plain prata)- $15 was on the high side.
Even if food inflation and the high rental had been incorporated inside, $15 was really expensive.
The saving grace, was the food was good. Nice prata. Including my ginger tea was nice.
Surprisingly, though I felt the prices were high, it was very crowded. Seemed the rest of the crowd were comfortable with the pricing.
Curry chicken rice! Pork rib rice and fried fish soup is the best!!!

Below average food for above average price. Steak was not very nice and pork chop was tough  but i like the consistency. Brocoli was okay but abit msgish. Wine was veryyyy bad and dry and non nice at all. Was not a good pairing with the beef
Professional service by the staff.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Chilli beef noodle was so-so. Same for the multi coloured XLBs.
The snacks are so good...
One of the best Halal restaurants in Singapore. Great food and service. Portion sizes are relatively big so good to share.

Decent Lok Lok, seasoning and chili is on point, and all the people tending the stall are friendly and polite. Sticks get refreshed often enough despite the demand. For those giving a low score based on the price and the queue and lack of seats, omg what is wrong with you people... this is 1) Singapore, and $1 a stick is reasonable; 2) this is a kopitiam for crying out loud!

During weekday lunchtime, table of 4 ordered a few dishes with rice. The plates of rice were served first served while we waited for more than 5 minutes for them to bring out the dishes while the rice turned cold. After we ate everything, it seemed that they forgot about our soup until we reminded the cashier. IMO, there must be customers who cancelled orders and left because of long wait. That was why they served rice to give us no reason to cancel orders while they take their time to cook the dishes.

content: Classic Chinese foods! Very delicious!

Prata is delicious, nasi goreng and pattaya are all delicious. A nice little restaurant at Kebun baru neighbourhood area. Nicely decorated. Not crowded during dinner time which is good. Will definitely visit often. Highly recommended üëç.

Just now i visit again to your sri sun express.  Ang mo kio Avenue 10.  Really totally Very bad experience again again. This time very terrible.  This time again same server. Excellent tasty Power Mee Rebus (Satay sauce)

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content:
Was even contemplating about giving 1 star as the customer service was beyond speechless - horrible. Bought a total of 8 pieces of sushi and asked if I could be given a pair of disposable chopsticks as I was intending to eat it outside and also for hygiene purpose.

However the reply given to me was, ‚Äúyour sushi are all of individual packaging so you do not require any chopsticks.‚Äù I was infuriated upon hearing that.

Ultra disappointed! This family run establishment is a real shame when next gen took over..gone r the glory days..

Love theirÁâπÈ¶ôÈ¶ôËèáÈù¢ÔºàNoodles in fragrant mushroom and minced pork sauce) and their shrimp and minced pork dumpling. My favourite orders everytime I visit the place. Love their outlet at Seletar Mall on weekdays m

Staff seems bored at work

Barramundi is ok. Gave feedback that Vegetable and mushroom is very salty but no respond from the manager. I had to drink lots of water to flush it down..

The Home made baked potatoes is good

Have visited this place about 5 times. Food is ok but you have to wait for really long just to get your food.

There are many staff but it seems like only one person cooking all the time. The restaurant may not be busy but food still takes real long to come. And sometimes after waiting for 15 mins for your food, they will still come and inform you that the water is boiling still or the chef had gone off for an emergency. And ask you if you would still like to carry on waiting. I‚Äôve tried giving them  benefit if the doubt but I think I‚Äôve learnt my lesson. Food will always be slow to come.

Excited to see shanghai dim sum resturant open close to United Square,  so can eat Shen Jian Bao nearby instead go to Ding Te Le which is far away from center.  Tried Shen Jian Bao and Xiao Long,  both nice and similar standard as Ding Te Le thats all I need.
Simply local breakfast or brunch üòä

Had a family dinner for 5 adults and 1 toddler on Saturday, 1 May, at 5 p.m. We were allowed in only when everyone arrives.

Dishes ordered included their famous Dang Kui Duck, lotus and pumpkin with salted egg sauce, pork ribs without bone, cha siu, and soup of the day. Every dish tasted great. Even the white rice was steamed to keep it tasting great while many restaurants are merely serving rice from a big rice cooker.

The only think that needs improvement is their Chinese tea, we ordered the pu er, individual serving.  Doesn't taste like high quality tea.

We loved the food so much that we signed up for the $88 membership to get $50x2 vouchers and 4 small dishes of their roast duck. A one time 20% off for birthday month voucher is also given. We will definitely go back again.

Superb quality indian cuisine. Located right between the junction of Upper Thomson road & Yio Chu Kang road.

They have air con seating on the inside & open area outside.

Ordered the $18.9 Lamb Shank to share. The best lamb shank I have tasted. The lamb doesn't have any single gamey taste or smell. The meat is just succulent tender & falls of the bone. They give a generous portion of basmati/biryani rice too. For the price I would say it can feed 2 pax.

Prata considered the crispier side which is totally my gem. $1.3 if I'm not wrong

The only down side to the place is that the teh tarik ice I ordered tasted very watered down even before the ice is melted into the milk tea.

Garlic butter nun $4.5 tasted light & fluffy but fragrant.

All the different curry I tasted tastes Abit on the sweet & sour side. (Mostly fish Curry if I'm not wrong) generally a decent standard restaurant price at a superb quality.
Amk Best Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee!!!
Just fried food, nothing special. Home made chilli sauce is nice though.

Customer service could be better, however food-wise, I'd give it a 7/10. Decent western food for a coffeshop under the HDB.

Be sure to try their Sweet Potato Fries, its one of my favorites from there.
Fast and efficient service. You can order online and wait for your turn to pick up your order. Not many seats available due to safe distancing.

Foods are very good. My favorite is fish soup üëçüëç but Whampoa is one of the dirtiest food court I have seen in Singapore . Very few staff to clean tables. If they can provide better cleaning in that food center would be so good place to go.
I was expecting good food because of the reviews here but the food was really really salty. I wasn't able to finish my Kampong fried rice. Even the lettuce dish is salty.
Came all the way from the east to try this out. Really good mutton murtabak. Curries accompanying the dish was really good too. Would definitely recommend!

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Great place to bring family for lunch or dinner fixed. Less crowded than the other outlets. The manager was very friendly and helpful enough to bring back to the kitchen to recook the steak that received raw initially.

The go to for dumplings, efficient service, delicious consistent food that all ages enjoy. Lemongrass drink has frozen lemongrass flavoured ice block, genius! We have a set preference when we go, but the range is wide. Most kids will love it too.
solid cheese and onion prata, and really nice butter chicken.
Great food and cool ambience

Great indian food. Jeera rice is so fragrant, it‚Äôs hard to eat just plain rice any more. All the dishes we ordered were fantastic.

The biggest problem was actually the beverage‚Ä¶ the ice tea was sad. ü•≤
Friendly service!
We have been patronising for years now. Their chilli ü¶Ä is üëçüèºüëçüèºüëçüèº

Definitely not your usual conveyor Japanese restaurant. We chanced on this hidden gem, located in the western part of Singapore. We ordered the salmon belly sashimi (Sake Harami) to share. Dish came with 6 slices of sashimi. The slices were thick and fresh. Immediately melted in my mouth. Damn delicious. Wifey and me then ordered a Deluxe Kaisen Don each. It‚Äôs a rice dish with egg, crab sticks, raw scallops, prawns, tuna and salmon. Topped with I believe salmon roe and uni (sea urchin). This dish was fabulous. It was so fresh and definitely filling. I washed it down with a nice bottle of warm sake. Abit pricey but definitely worth every dollar. Will recommend not to order too many dishes first as the portion is pretty big and the richness of the dishes will leave you satisfied quickly. Ample parking available so no worries about parking.
The Indian cuisine is fabulous! My first time trying out and I am amazed by the flavour and quality of food.

restaurant name: Choo Chiang Roasted Ducks & Cooked Food Pte Ltd - Sengkang
content: bad customer service. food soso, price insanely high
Good food

Frills-free restaurant cum cafe that sells western and Nepalese food. The food is not too bad but the service is commendable, the staff were eager to serve and friendly. There are set meals to choose from; daily ones, student and even for senior citizens (60 and above). I enjoyed the butternut squash soup, their signature ribs (fall-off-the-rack, hickory sauce?), Sausage (juicy!) lemon tea and colesaw. Apart from that, the sides of fries was normal and mashed potato a little too dry, the steak could be more seasoned and the mushroom sauce was just ok (maybe the other sauces are better). Other than baramundi, the fish used (such as in the grilled fish and fish and chips) was mushy but i guess you get what you pay for? The tiramisu was tasty and more of a well-set cake. If I do visit again, would want to try the Nepalese food here. If you want coffee, perhaps should try Shrove Tuesday among the opposite row of shops which sells waffles and coffee.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: all the staff working here are very attentive towards customers !! food is all at reasonable price. will definitely go back again if me and my friends crave for mooks !! üòãüòã

SO
YUMMY
Customer service is terrible. They won‚Äôt listen to ur order properly. Their food is mediocre but a little overpriced.
Love the food here.

Decent Japanese food. Ordered tonkotsu & duxk ramen, broth was tasty. Kakiage was not crispy though, it felt too much flour. Curry was also so so. The restaurant only have 1 female staff taking order, serving food & cashier. Kudos to her that despite the hectic, she still maintained her smile & ever helpful.

Authentic and affordable shanghainese street food in a chic, modern compact setting. Pan fried buns and the drunken chicken were the highlight of the meal. The food here does not align with local taste buds, and hence the poor reviews. So come in here with an open mind and you'll might begin to appreciate true shanghainese cooking style. Fast and efficient service, it has one of the most intuitive qr ordering system I've ever came across.
Chicken katsu curry ramen. Good and reasonable.

We opted for self pick up at a specific timing half a day in advance.
However, when I arrived and said that I'm here to pick up my food, they then began to cook.
Had to wait an additional 15-20mins for my food to be cooked which caused me to be late for a family dinner.

It would've been nice if they prepared and had the food cooked and ready to go by the timing given.

We ordered the P1 platter combo and the M9 spicy sausage.

The platter was decent but the chicken was pretty good.

Spicy sausages were nice too however, it didn't come with the mash potatoes as shown in the picture.

Overall, I'd say it's still a pretty decent meal!
The ginger tea was good. Didn't try the food therefore unable to comment.
Food is nice and fresh! thumb up for the services too! üëçüèªüëçüèª recommend to family and friends gatherings! üòä

Had to come here because passed by Toa Payoh area and didn't make any reservation for lunch. Food quality is alright, can't fault them on this, we had soup dumplings, been sprout, roast pork for 4 and 1/2 a roast chicken. Didn't go for duck, and char siew ran out. We just order anything that came to mind because our party of 4 is pretty hangry. Pricing wise, yes they didn't have prices listed and the bill came to be slightly higher than your avg hawker or kopitiam roast meat stall but not entirely unreasonable (avg. S$13 per pax including a drink each). Would I come here again? Perhaps, only after I have tried other places along the food alley stretch here...

Decided to go there for dinner since many years haven't tried.
No menu and price list to order from, and specifically told the staff that we wanted small portions of roasted duck, roasted meat and char siew, dumpling soup, 2 plate of rice and one plain noodle.
When they served, it was one quarter duck, and another plate of roasted pork and char siew which seemed to be able to serve 4-5 when there are only 3 of us.
And come with the bill of almost $43 for 3 of us! Probably the most expensive roasted meat that I have ever taken, other than Kam's Roast.
Some of the reviews commented that it is like black shop (ÈªëÂ∫ó) which I would not deny having that feeling too.
On a fair note, the food is not bad but does not justify the exorbitant prices.
There is a lady who seemed to be the lady boss, seated there and busy with her accounts (maybe calculating how much money they have grabbed), and with rather poor attitude.
I would have given one star, but decided to give one more for the old uncle and old auntie for their good service.

They said here got thai style cook n I double confirm and waiter said true..  I go n order bihun tomyam, but taste not like thai style at all... hmm I'm so disappointed üò≠ but I'm still finish my meal üòÜ I'm just don't like to do a  wasted ..
Good for family and friends meal together. Food delicious. Loved the Braised Yellow üíõ Croacker fish the most.  And the fried Yellow Croacker. Excellent ! Cooked to perfection üòã

Amazing Resto for Indian food . Owner is very interacting and very friendly staff are good usually busy in afternoon and night ... Food is tasty well effort made my management.... had a great experience....
Hearty bowl of ramen at a very reasonable price. Definitely worth the trip all the way from the East! Highly recommended! Oh yes, must try their Gyoza too.
Food is horrible especially the Bara Chirashi Sakana Don, the rice  Is very soggy and sticks together like a clump
Delicious, good quality breakfast with cheap price, long queue but fast service.. need more chair and table for dine in..

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Very delicious cuisine, but be prepared to wait if u dine in

Let's see... How much would you have been charged to eat such street food in Bangkok. I was under the influence that if you had ordered a fish, a meat, a veg and an egg... You will be looking at 50 bucks in bkk. Well, I was filled at 45ish and 4 pax. What else is there to complain?  The portions are decent, the taste is authentic. I don't know what others are looking at for their Thai food. But I tasted Thailand the moment I entered the place.

Unassuming place that serves decent roti prata. What's interesting is that the prata is served with 2 different curries as well as sambal ikan bilis.
One curry is the regular type served with  prata; it's not bad, but watered down. The second curry is loaded with spices, not the chilli or pepper kind of spice, more like cardamom and turmeric, etc. It's interesting cos at the other places I've tried that serves 2 curries, one would usually be curry and the other would be dahl.
This is my first visit to Meera's; and judging from the rather extensive menu, I suspect that their prata, while decent enough, is not their specialty. I'm sure some of their dishes must be great, or they wouldn't have more than one branch. If I'm in the area again, I may return and try out some other dishes.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content:
First try frozen chicken essence
simple into a bowl, steam it in a rice cooker with 40ml of water in the outer pot for 5-8 mins.
bowl of chicken essence every morning,

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Good place for late night snack. Prata is good. Freshly made.
Good, reasonably priced western food.  The BBQ PorkRibs tasted awesome, garlic fish nice too.
Clean and spacious. The kiosk machine was operating with a enough distance during this COVID sensitive time.

If you want to have something cheap and yummy, please give this store a try. Here for the 6th time and the food standard keeps improving. Although they may be quite slow with their service, it‚Äôs honestly worth the wait.

Just hope the management can look into the lack of manpower here. I always see 1 staff rushing to grill the meat, do the cashiering, clear the tables, pour the drinks for the customers...... Hope their pay is worth the amount of stress they have been through.
Queue already started when it opens. The portion is generous and the gravy is nice. However the chicken is bland in flavour.

A delightful and enjoyable dining experience!
All the dishes were on point.
Got a complimentary birthday dessert too!
Great service from the friendly host, Zamzi.
Would definitely come back here again.
Great Halal Wine on the special day with my hubby. Good Food and Good view and serenity.

Alright sushi in AMK Hub with an alright price point. Interior design is cute and clean. Food quality varies vastly between different sushi. Most of the sushi we had were pretty alright, with the exception of the yellowtail which tasted really dry and weird. Also because of their train system, some of their sushi arrives toppled. Another flaw would be that the 2 pax table is a little small after all the tea and shoyu and tissue box taking up the space, meaning that you can't order too many plates at once. Then again their sushi comes really slowly and one at a time. Waiting time could be improved. One of our orders was also forgotten by the kitchen and had to remind the staff about it, but due to lack of staff it was hard to get their attention.

I'm totally disappointed with the service and regretted coming all the way just to have my first time experience with Sushi-GO yesterday. We reached there around 1:45pm, long queue found outside Sushi-GO and was told by one of the male staff that is the the queue to take queue number and need to wait around 3 - 4 hours to dine in after getting a queue number. I don't mind waiting for a few hours, by then it could be dinner time. I got my queue number at 1:57PM for queue number A276, there is still long queue behind me. I spent my time walking around,  went for movie etc. At 3:55PM, the queue number is only A052. ! came back at 6pm. I asked one of the female staff at the counter, the queue isn't really moving, what if we cannot dine in today? Can we get a compensation like a queue number for tomorrow? She answered, they didn't expect such an overwhelmed response. The queue started as early at 9AM this morning. There is no time limit for dine in so customers tend to eat slower, chit chat. They can't give me queue number for tomorrow as it is a first come first serve basis. I'm like? So you want me to come all the way here to try my luck AGAIN? I replied, by doing all these no one will want to even come back for such service. Long waiting time. Not getting dine in. No compensation. We overheard that the queue number got until 500ish till they stop taking in. At 9PM, we received a message from Sushi-GO that they are calling our queue. We can join Hungry Ghost Festival if we have waited till 9PM for our dinner.
Food is awesome. Friendly staff. Downside is just small and limited  seating area. Cleanliness is good.
The dishes were delicious, get the deep fried fish, I crunched and swallowed the backbone. The Nonya and Baba flavours are fresh, tantalising - real authentic and wallet friendly.
Friendly staff and tasty food. Great place for family or friends

It's a spacious cafe with welcoming staff. Ordered the mentaiko fries - which was great for sharing. The salmon was well executed but we didnt really appreciate the rosti. Overall, its a nice find in the area.

Did not expect their specialty dish "Claypot chicken" was so delicious that bought back my old memories of home cooked food.
This restaurant was managed by group of friendly aunties who provide efficient and fast services. Turn around table was fast and crowded

Having walked pass the shop for so long, finally a visit. Very busy this particular evening. Extensive menu with not so many Teochew dishes. Food was ordinary tasting by me. Duck's braising liquid could do with stronger flavors. Kway teow lacked wok hei. Orr jiang was overly starchy for my liking. Sugar coated yam was fantastic! Just as I remembered when granny had made these many moons ago. Siew Mai filled with prawns instead of pork or fish paste was a wonderful delight, like ones you will find in a proper cantonese restaurant. Being very reasonably priced dining here makes it up. So it's a mix bag of hits and misses in here. Shall look forward to try the rest of their menu offerings.
Nice food,friendly staff and affordable pricing
The food was better than average, but wasn't particularly spectacular.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: All their steamed stuff like xiao long bao and cheecheong fan had v thick skin which im not a fan of. But the prawn beancurd deep fried dish was da bomb. Best in SG i‚Äôve tried. Generally v flavourful.

Ordered the Set D chicken rice with pepper pig intestine soup.  Not impressive. Soup tasted like pepper water, ginger paste was watery.   Staff chatting non stop next to my table, couldn't have a relaxing lunch after a busy morning. Environment is very clean and cozy.Overall experience, 2/5.

Had dim sum lunch here. Overall food and services was good but was disappointed by 12pm no more roast pork as they have limited quantity. Better to make reservation and inform them in advance if you wan roast pork.

Staff was friendly and attentive. I was the second customer in the restaurant so the food was served very fast. Alice who served my table was prompt with request a humble hard working staff. Peking duck was roasted skilfully. The skin was light and fluffy but the meat marination was not good enough some part of it we can still taste a gamy smell. Spring onion and cucumber was a little dry. No presentation the wrap was all stack up in a pile served on a side plate $40 standard I can‚Äôt complain. The prawn cake was nice and crispy. The hot and sour soup and braised shark fin soup was both very starchy can‚Äôt taste much of the soup base. Green veg was decent. The worst is their signature deep fried honey coated mushroom. Full of flour! Wonder where the mushroom go? The credit and saviour of the dinner is their O NEEE.... the yam paste dessert. Smooth... melt in your mouth. Will be back there again for Chinese New Year eve dinner hope the festive dishes will be more appealing and appetising.
Very disappointed n felt cheated by the restaurant. What show in the menu is different from what I buy home. No ü•¶, no Thai sauce dou fu

The area was located near Old Upper Thomson road, where there were open carparks for parking. Convenience was of concern when we reached there. Service staff were friendly and nice, as we made our reservations through phone. We ordered the 6 persons value set meal together with an extra fried rice for our kids. Food taste were surprisingly tasty and  the portion were huge!. That was a plus point given our first time patronizing the stall. Price wise was a bit on the high side with Service charge and GST imposed, hence a 4 star review for the restaurant. Good to revisit again for the tasty food served.

The food had always been the best. It was always been a great pleasure dine in, takeaway or been catered. Rahim have never failed to ensure we leave with a smile. I am 101% glad with the fingerlicking sedap food and ambience created by the staffs there. Kudos to all of you for giving us a different level of flavours without coloring added.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Food and service was üëç, black Pepper must and shark fin soup must try ÔøΩ ‚Ä¶
Pretty decent Lok Lok, priced at $1 per stick with a variety of sauces (which you can choose 2). I particularly liked that they offer mantou cos who doesn't like a good fried bun right?

Super yummy and tasty!! Reasonably priced! Love the steamed dumplings as well as pan fried ones. The fried pizza dumpling was not bad too. Zha jiang mian was super tasty and love that it was peanut butter sauce! Highly recommend this place for a casual dinner :)
Salted Egg Prawn Burger

Always here for their Teh Halia (less sugar), gingery and spicy enough.
Prata is usually alright, pretty standard. Sometimes I'll get the honey tissue prata to snack on while chit-chatting.
Thosai is a good choice too.

From review, this restaurant seems good so here we are to try.

Indeed the food is good and not crowded too:)

A lot of variety towards the food:)

Most importantly, a good chance to chit chat with family:)

We tried the following:
„ÄãButashoga Ramen | Their signature shio-tonkotsu broth topped with hand-pulled pork saut√©ed in a sweet soy sauce and ginger was absolutely delish, I totally understand now why it's one of their bestsellers. The balanced flavours coming from the rich soup, saucy meat, sweetness from the braised bamboo shoots and green scallions was delightful.

„ÄãMiso Ramen | Such a hearty ramen which was infused with a generous amount of roasted Hokkaido red miso tonkotsu soup base, perfectly paired with the various toppings of sweet corn, slow-braised chashu pork slices, thinly sliced green scallions and beansprouts. The robust medley of flavours were simply delectable.

„ÄãTakoyaki | These Octopus Balls had a pillowy filling complimented by the mayonnaise, Japanese BBQ sauce and seaweed toppings. I took a mouthful and the flavours just bursted in my mouth, so addictive.

„ÄãDeep Fried Gyoza | Crispy deep-fried dumplings which had a substantial amount of chicken/veggie filling.

„ÄãChilli Crab Matcha Macchiato with Fresh Milk (New) | Being adventurous at heart, I instantly knew that I had to give this one a go once I saw it on the menu. It was quite (weird) unique and certainly not for the faint-hearted! Try it for yourselves if you're brave enough like me ~
Always nice food! Today's best food is the salted egg crab!!üòã
Average food. Better to travel to Teluk Intan for the original. There is nothing special about the mee. The Assam laksa is good.
Only left with halal Indian stall called Bagus ria. No halal western food. Only stall Bello says no pork no lard.
Waited for 45 mins for mediocre food and non-existent service. Sushi was overcharged and some of the orders didn't come. No apology given and no service recovery. First visit also my last visit.

Was craving for coin prata, but it turned out to be just mini kosong prata. Not buttery, not fluffy, not sweet... it's just smaller kosong prata, but higher price. Other than that, the rest of the normal kosong prata still acceptably crispy.
Very nice and delicious chicken rice. Fully recommended to give a try.

Finally got to try the legendary 24h ramen raved about by Steven Lim korkor and it was top tier‚Ä¶on the list of most mediocre fast food style ramen. We got the karakamen + egg + cha shu and it was most certainly a hearty supper. I like that the cha shu slices are thin and relatively tender, though you‚Äôll have to soak the extra pieces in the broth for a while to get some added flavor.

The only disappointment is that the soup is not hot enough after we poured everything into it and it's at the temperature of tongue. Chilli oil can be much better and sesame oil should be provided too. My 2 cents.

I don't think the lady's service attitude is very good, I have given her three chances. I think the boss should educate your employees about their service attitude. If her service attitude is like this, I advise her not to do front desk service. - From traditional Penang food.

My wife and I went there for a weekend dinner. It was underneath a block of hdb flat which is uncommon but the service was prompt and the place was very family friendly (read: grandparents munching the life out of the drumstick, children monkeying around with mums keeping a watchful eye, dads with dismissive looks or have the eyes glued to their smartphones or the newspaper).

It looks more like a saizeriya restaurant than a Chinese restaurant but this food place brings me back esp the chicken.

Reasonably priced, good quick service, tasty rice and chicken, good for families.

Had the October promo. Ordered 1 main and free 2 side. October special pork platter usual price $30 plus going for $15. Very big portion and super value for money.

Highly recommanded. Love the fried squid and the marinate. Service is excellent and friendly.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
One of more spaceious and clean hawkers in Sg. Few key personal fav stalls to try..
1) qing qing kopi shop
2) shredded chicken fishball noodle
3) teowchew dimsum
4) uggly muffins
5) hk roast
6) chee chong fun

Enjoy !
Hidden gem at the basement of Square 2. Ordered the green chilli chicken set super yummy. They are Halal certified and serve Thai food as well!

Having a meal here is worth all the cravings. The Cheese Prata is very crispy and the curry has a subtly sweet but savoury taste. The Cheese Prata tastes very excellent and is full of cheese. The Chicken Biryani also tastes very delicious. All the curries have an authentic taste. The Teh Cino is not too sweet but it has a very pleasant taste of tea and milk.
Very nice ambience and good food. Mr Sara is so courteous and customer centric person and Ms Skyler is so prompt in her service.

I had their classic series Bi Feng Tang Fish and Chips (I requested to change out the corn cob for coleslaw) and it tasted fresh and great! It was well-fried, not too dry and oily üëçüëçThe garlic crumbs topping enhanced the overall taste and aroma of the fish! No fishy smell at all! Received good customer service from the team too, especially the malay lady (didn‚Äôt managed to get her name) üëçüëç
Worst food and waste of money

There were only 2 pieces of pork ribs given for a $18 spanish pork ribs set‚Ä¶ i finished the meat in 2 bites.

Fish was good and portion was good.
Just had the burrito bowl with pulled pork for lunch. Really good and the pork was so tender! A tad on the salty side but the corn chips helped!!

Found this shop/restaurant by itself below a MSCP at Yishun, in a corner.
The environment is neat and tidy, quiet.
Enjoyed it's quietness, peace, tranquility.

Food is just slightly above average, not tried all menu yet, but had 2 egg prata and a teh tarik.
Prata was springy, not crunchy.
Teh tarik was almost tasteless, water ratio too much, little taste of tea.
Nasi lemak, $3, comes with fried chicken wing, egg and ikan bilis. Chili is spicy and rice is rich in coconut milk aroma.

Should be a family run business.
Food is good at its prices.
Dont think anything is expensive, even buy school standards. Burgers are abit pricier but a big hefty burger

Sides were nice too

Don't you just love it when planned things go wrong and the unplanned becomes a gem of a place?
That's what happened to my wife and I earlier this evening. We drove down to Sembawang to eat dinner at the Chong Pang Nasi Lemak place. It was closed.
We walked along the row of shophouses, and chanced upon this Indian restaurant.
We both love Indian food, so we walked in, sat down and I scoured the dishes in their counter and the ones in their menu.

Arabic rice, not bryani, I was told. Long grains of yellow rice with spice and raisins inside, accompanied by piquant, slightly spicy, super melt-in-the-mouth mutton in curry, and a bowl of my favourite Indian Tom Yum, rasem! Aromatic happy meal at its very best.
Wife had the paper thin, crispy garlic naan, with fish curry, and we shared some fish cutlets, cauliflower 65 (yup! Not chicken 65), and tau-kwa in sambal.
We're both so delighted we found this place! The food's great, the people inside warm and Very Friendly, and a dinner bill that didn't raise my eyebrows. Mind you, this doesn't happen too often these days, when everything is so pricey!

Cheap food, good food, and great service! I can't find any fault with this place! Give it a try! You won't regret it üòò
Ordered from grab. Very disappointed. Rice is too soggy. Teriyaki chicken has no sauce & meat is too hard too. Pork katsu is too dry. Salmon is overcooked. One of the worse that I encountered.
Not much choice of food after 2am.....but still service is good
Limited time high tea set promotion during 3pm to 5pm is highly recommended. Laksa selling at 2.9 during this period
Nice zi chai..good service
When it first open at seletar mall, I was hoping it will open on JP. After one year, they finally did. Love the food there. Staff Are friendly too on my 3 visits...
Great food at affordable prices. Requires qr code scanner to view menu for most places

Deep fried sea bass was overfried, sea bass wasn't the freshest, the gravy was overpowering and not too yummy. Deep fried pork had a faint taste of frozen pork. Stir fried kailan was too salty and too sweet. Not worth a second visit.
They have great roti prata, cheap Indian Vegie Meal and other good stuff in general

The fried chicken is nice and juicy though on the smaller size. It‚Äôs very economical that for $3.50 you get a meat, an egg, peanuts and anchovies.

However I didn‚Äôt fancy the rice with mushy texture and coconut flavour quite like. Also the chilli is not spicy. As other said, abit like Chinese Nasi lemak

So if you Wan to try non spicy Nasi lemak. This is it. And yes there‚Äôs a queue even on weekdays

(Translated by Google) The dishes are very delicious! Order Spicy Chicken and Spicy Chicken. Highly recommended!

(Original)
The dishes are very delicious! Order Ëæ£Â≠êÈ∏° and Âè£Ê∞¥È∏°. Highly recommended!
Fantastic service. Ordered Dan Dan Mian, Sichuan  chilli chicken and prawns. Great ambience and rates are very reasonable. Total value for money.

Great black pepper chicken chop, must try it.
The chicken is well done and black pepper sauce is awesome.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: last week Friday they give spoiled  briyani I'm I eat now I get  food poison  ,, now I have medical expenses  61.5
Food stall run by a Thai couple. Food was good. Not too expensive. Recommended.

Decent food, small menu, and fast service.

Chinese pizza (9/10)
Savoury pastry pie with dumpling fillings. The crust was crunchy and super yummy, and their seafood, pork-spring onion filling was also packed with flavour. Would definitely order this again.

Steamed dumplings (7/10)
Wasn‚Äôt particularly tasty, not bad.

Zha Jiang Noodles (6/10)
Handmade doughy noodles coated with *sweet* peanut sauce. Imagine peanut butter + noodles. Noodles were overcooked (soggy) instead of al Dante. Dish felt more like a dessert.
Service level is great!  Food tastes great! Located in hdb and may look humble from the outside but the Chinese food quality is definitely comparable or better than a five star hotel's restaurant.

Old-school comfort Western food best eaten on the spot. Tried the black pepper beef slices with rice and found the beef succulent and not too tough. The black pepper sauce was not too overwhelming and paired well with the beef. The buzzer system also makes ordering and waiting very orderly so overall a very pleasant experience üëçüëç
Very disappointed that the roti prata and curry is served hard and cold. Hope they can improve this.
Nice place for lunch with colleagues. The braised pork is very tasty, small portion is enough for 1 person (the large portion is definitely for sharing).

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: I loved ur briyani . My son‚Äôs loved fried rice and fresh juice . Looking nice place . Service too good . üëçüëåüèºüòãüçπ. Filter coffee so tasty üòã
There is a lot of add in and option which made the price higher. The food is getting worse than before.
Wow. Amazing curry, soft potatoes, nice sesame filling ball, and fluffy prata. Highly recommended.
Nice Atmosphere!!! Friendly Staffs

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: It sells nice Muslim food. Down side is very limited of park lots. Do not dine in during lunch time, difficult to get seats especially during Covid-19 endemic. Enjoy the good food!!! Matey!!!
Very nice food,I‚Äôm the daily customer in d‚Äôrubinah,very delicious Makan,very friendly staff and drinks very nice,superbüòãüíïüëåüëåüëåüëå‚ù§Ô∏è

Eatery serving traditional pratas and also pratas with a nice twist. The salted egg & prawn murtabak is a must try! The portion size for their murtabak is huge. We ordered the mini size for 2 murtabak, prata coins (5 mini plain pratas), mutton curry and drinks, and we (3 pax) can barely finish it. Definitely a great place for a hearty breakfast or supper.
hire more ppl during exam weekends!!

This humble restaurant tucked at a little corner is really a gem. Recommended by a friend. A small cozy restaurant with limited seats. Service was great and food was excellent, definitely have the home taste.
We ordered vegetarian and chicken masala set with a side dish of prawn masala. Food was served promptly. Nice to go with a cup of ‚Äòtea halia‚Äô.
Will definitely return to try the remaining dishes.

Don‚Äôt go by Its long list of menu and the name that states it‚Äôs Indian. The prices are cheap but the food pathetically made. The mutton that we had was too hard to chew. The restaurant needs to improve a lot on its hygiene. They didn‚Äôt even provide a printed bill or break up of the items ordered. Cards don‚Äôt work here.

Grilled "Fish" with Sichuan Mala Broth

First attracted by the photo and now charmed by the taste!!!
Very "FISH" !!!
Goes so well with the Mala Broth
Spiciness is just right,  watch out for the hemp pepper!!! It will numb your tongue and lips!!! üò´

Luckily the Ice Blended Soursop calm down the numbness  üòÖ

Kannan and his team were attentive to us the whole evening - ensuring that our needs were met and that everything was fine. The food was lovely too. Love the portion size so that we can try a greater variety of food too. However, big eaters may have to order more to fill their stomachs. We enjoyed the barramundi and sea bass as they are different from the usual. We love the kurobuta ribs too - soft, tender and falls off the bone. The children enjoyed the thin udon with tonkatsu broth so much that they were arguing for a second helping :) love the ambience and thank you for accommodating the children!

Thank you for the lovely evening!

Pad Thai here didn't resemble pad Thai at all, they used the ipoh hor fun kind of kuey teow and ended up in a mushy mess. Pork satay here was nicely marinated and barbecued but have very fatty layers, price is also on the steep side considering that it is located in a coffee shop. The stalls here are inaccessible for wheelchair user because of the huge step and narrow pathways, only seats at the outer part of the coffee shop are accessible.

Tried Blue Pea Flower Nasi Lemak @ Lotus Vegatarian. This is one of the best vegetarian nasi lemak you can find. The sambal is nice and not too spicy. Furthermore the sambal was put inside a small plate which I always hope other restaurant can follow this method because this cam prevent the oil from sambal flood into the rice. Thumbs up for the food presentation.
Kimchi grilled pork rice bowl was not very worth it, pork slices were tender and grilled super well with that nice char but quite few. The kimchi was also such a meagre pathetic portion.

Took my mom and a few other family members for their dim sum tea on a Sunday afternoon.

I've been here before a while back (used to bring clients here) and dim sum is still the same quality. For those coming here for the first time, expect quite an old-school Chinese interior with service provided by a body of older staff - food still came pretty fast.

We ordered the Har Gao (standard quality - shrimp is pretty fresh), Beancurd Roll (a tad too elastic and starchy for me, but my mom thought it was good), Xiao Long Bao (nice healthy mouthfuls with very delicate skin - fair quality and taste for at $5.40 per basket of 3), Beef Brisket Congee (very smooth congee, and very soft beef - better than the generic lean pork century egg congee), Char Siew Chee Cheong Fun (I prefer the ones at Tim Ho Wan, the skin is smoother and char siew is of better quality), half an Irish Roasted Duck (fantastic crispy skin with well-roasted fats), Asparagus stir-fried with Scallops (no photos, ate it too fast!) and salted egg yolk buns for dessert (these come baked in a delicious thin crust and loads of filling).

I gave it only 4 stars out of 5 because they only informed us the Irish duck was not included under the Chope Voucher promo (we paid $35 per $50 voucher, basically 30% discount) only after we had ordered everything (and we declared we were using the vouchers right from get go) and was midway through the dim sum, despite the T & C's in the Chope Vouchers stating that all a la carte menu items were included in the promo. I did feedback to the staff at the end of the meal that this is something they can improve upon, and chose to use only 2 out of 3 Vouchers I had prepared for this meal instead.

4 adults and 1 child (who ate as much as the adults) cost us around $140 with a value of $170.

Will just have to come back for the Xiao Long Bao and the Salted Egg Yolk buns!
The number of seats/tables are limited. But not crowded even on Sat night. Food were ok, taste just suit us.

(Translated by Google) This is a super comfortable place especially when you come over in the afternoon.

When they have fewer customers. They will allow you to sit in as long as you want.

The food is so authentic and yummy. And can choose your spicy level.

Lao ban niang so nice also, will always do her best to attend to our special requests.

Didn't expect much before coming. I never thought that a Sichuan restaurant could be so delicate and beautiful. The lady boss is really awesomeüëçüèª

And the moment I sit down, I feel so comfortable, so casual, I can really sit there and work all afternoon.

And the point is that the food is delicious, but only if you can eat spicy foodü§™ But there are also several special dishes that children can eat.
