3 food stalls, including 1 halal Western food. A few other stalls have recently closed.
New kid on the block, with fried rice that packs a punch
Super food

Had dinner here with a friend, order beancurd on hotplate and steam fish. The beancurd was good but the fish was lacking. As my friend cannot take spicy food so ended up choosing the non spicy cooking. Price wise decent, payment type they take grab pay.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Nice and tasty food! Fresh and good. Worth the price, definitely will be back again!

We are honored to be invited to a wine pairing dinner at Xi Yan by Wine List Asia.

The theme of the food for that night was Chinese food fusion with some Japanese elements. It went well with wine from Satori and we all had a insightful discussion on how each of the wine has its own unique characteristics and how versatile they were.

What I like about the restaurant is it‚Äôs interior decor and personal collection of porcelains, pottery and tea ware of the owner.w

We enjoyed the dinner with great company and good wine from Satori by Wine List Asia. The wines made the food enjoyable.

6 Jun '22:
Return visit so I could try their mala soup version. I had it medium spiciness and it was excellent. Almost addictive. More la and less ma, which I find a deviation of original mantra of Sichuan cuisine.
Nonetheless, it was excellent meal.

5 Jun '22:
Had a hard time trying to find the place. This hideout had both indoor (air con) and outdoor. Good vibes and cosy environment.
A huge variety to choose from.
Ordered both the less- and medium- spicy levels. The medium spicy level has a good kick and numbness to it.
The must-haves are potato, lotus root, beancurd skin, cuttlefish balls and whole fish. They have other proteins such as chicken and pork but they do not label them.
Ask for the reward card which they give 1 stamp for every $15 spent.
Free parking after 6pm.
Order the daily set meal. It Wass served real fast. Not totally full house even at lunch time.
Chinese pizza, steamed/ pan fried dumplings were all good! Zha jiang noodle was a peanut sauce instead of meat sauce so a tad sweet for my liking. No frills, small menu and consistent :)

Nice and made to order fresh prata. Curry sauce is nice and thick. The ice teh Tarik is sweet & thick. The Horlick Godzilla is unique. The murtabak is delicious and savoury. How I prefer it cut in squares instead of triangles. Overall recommended.

Aunt  talking say give free face mask last when pay money say $1/- plus the order total add up, feel like the word can't believe from the start. Feeling so bad hearing negative sorry you need to pay second sentence :(
Overall nice place. Can choose a seat near screen during weekends for soccer matches.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: There are variety of dim sum to choose from. The usual time to wait for the steaming time and served. Skin of the dim sum is think and taste good from the inner content.
Can't travel to Malaysia? This will do for now. For me, I had hard time deciding what to eat. Everything looked so good. Finally settled for penang kway teow. Had nice wokhei taste.

Chicken chop at $7.90 comes with two sides (I swopped fries for coleslaw). Very generous portion, meat was the perfect thickness, well seared and piping hot (I've had enough of lukewarm chicken chop precooked in bulk). Top that off with a cheery and friendly server and that gives you every reason for supporting this stall.

My picture doesn't do it justice (took in hurry as I was hungry) but I'd recommend those who are in the area to give it a try. Extensive menu choices and I'm sure you'll find something that catches your eye.

Teh tarik is not bad. And I also like the tosai masala there. The filling sometimes a lot some times a little. The rice and curry is also good.

Edit: Jun 13th, idk what this is, looks like uneatable

Cheap cheerful and they are everywhere!!! Someone should bring this franchise to Melbourne please!!! The kopi could be slightly a bit less sweet but is still pretty good! Love the sotong and also had their curry puffs!! if only I had a second stomach!
Awesome food Awesome ambience üî•üî•üî•, Great place to hang out & chill. This is definitely also a must visit for all naruto fans out there! üôåüèªüôåüèª
The food is great. sizeable portions, excellent.

Wow.. love this place for its space... wide spacious and hippy green ambience... Nice!

Simply the space and deco makes this cafe super comfortable to laze and chill in.

And I'm glad the great food goes well with ambience too..

Been here twice already. And their pastas and burger is great!

And their online loyalty program is definitely tempting me to go back a 3rd 4th time...
And its only tempting because food and ambience is great..

Would definitely be back many more times
Great food

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Ordered crispy squid, cheese sauce prawns, spicy chilli horfun, charcoal grilled korabuta and some special beehoon. Only the crispy squid and korabuta were pretty fine. The cheese sauce prawn was poor. The prawns seemed to have attempted a ‚Ä¶

Journey to the North for affordable Putien Food. Aside from the must order Heng Hua Style Fried Bee Hoon & Heng Hua Style Lor Mee, highly recommended to try their Stir-Fried Sliced Yam. The Yam cubes are slightly crispy on the outside coated with some sweet sauce while it‚Äôs soft and mushy inside. I can just order this as a meal for myself, it‚Äôs so good!
.
Location: Heng Hua Restaurant, Yishun Street 72, #01-212 Block 748, Singapore 760748
Food was nice.

Me and my wife was scouting for a great crab place around amk. This shop did not disappoint me at all. Even tho we did not order crab ( because we wanted to test those other dishes first) we will definitely be back for the crab.
This is April 2021. The food quality really improved so as the price range. May be due to new management. Now average price of lunch is 7$
Standard drop very dramatically

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: amazing flavour!

This stall has no name, so its "signboard" just says "Western Food". Located in S-11 hawker center, which is the one just beside Jubilee Square. There is only 1 western stall, so it's quite easy to spot. One of the few underrated Western food stalls in hawker centers.

I've been here quite a few times and I must say I like the really generous portions and affordable price. A usual chicken chop at $6.5 gets you the chicken chop, fries, garlic bread, baked beans and coleslaw. Portion is easily visible in my photo.
I got the photo of the salted egg yolk fried chicken cutlet. Too fried for my liking, but still a sinful and enjoyable meal overall. Salted egg yolk sauce is a bit little, but it was quite thick.

The auntie used to be a bit rude since last time, and customer service was bad as well. But over the years I've observed improvement. And who cares about bad attitude, as long as the food is good right? (Cues those expensive restaurants with bad service staff attitude)
Those days where you feel like having a cheat day/meal? üòú Yeap this is right where you wanna go to.

Finally we are back to Sushi Tei NPC outlet.
Something is missing...Zuwai Crab & Seafood Fried Rice from the menu which is the all time sold out in SG as it is really one of the best fried rice I have ever tasted.
But You can try Zuwai Gani Chawanmushi.

Hainanese chicken is juicy n tender, however the rice a dispointment, the rice grain they use can be of better quality. The braised soft peanut is a great appetiser. The restaurant also have zi char menus which I think they have a good selection of dish. It is located next to a open air carpark.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: So far, I've tried Lontong and Mee Hoon Soto. Both are nice. Sambal tumis not very spicy, which is good. Their epok2 sardine is a must try. Tasty n ample of sardine inside.
Good place for beer, but now cannot due to heightened alert phase, can only order take away

Overall not bad. Just that portions are small.
Must get the giant prawns.
One thing they can add is the option for special requests cos I realise a lot of their dishes are with mayonnaise.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: I love the food here , cheap and good reasonable price and delicious . My favourite is Hor Fun 4.5 $ serving in a full plate , The aroma of rice noodles stir-fried is so nice.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Horrible service given, I usually don‚Äôt post reviews but this is the worst branch ever. To make reservations as well, they just left you seen on blue tick without confirming if your reservation is made. When you reach there, they said they didn‚Äôt get the reservation üòÖ truly poor service

Visited Putien multiple times .
This is the first time during CNY .
There were a few packages for CNY set meal.
Food was good . Service is excellent üëåüèª
Definitely worth to try at least once for authentic Putien cuisine üëçüèª

Not bad, gives you a good feel of what food in Nepal is like. Most interesting to me was the dumpling. Eating it like Chinese style with Indian curry.

I celebrated my wedding anniversary here and ordered lovely dishes. We ordered four dishes: Fried Lion's mane mushroom, Crispy Sichuan chicken, Iberico pork cheek and braised Sichuan tofu. My favourite was the Lion's mane mushroom. It was simply delicious. The service was very good, maybe the restaurant was mostly empty. If the restaurant is full, one may experience staff shortage. Overall, nice experience.
Love this cosy Japanese  casual restaurant.    Food exceeded my expectation especially the champion floss maki and aburi... affordably priced and great service from staff

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Tried their famous Fried Fish Beehoon with XO sauce, it was really very delicious. The fish slices were fresh and thick. The fish broth coupled with the milk, was very flavorful and of course with the addition taste of XO, it enhanced it totally, making the fish soup so fabulous. Definitely worth coming down here for their Fish Beehoon with XO sauce.
Nice place fir makan2 should try. Thumps up.

Overly priced. Small piece of tandoori chicken cost SGD 6.00 &  too salty. . Ice Lemon Tea 3 dollars. If the drink comes bigger cup is acceptable but it's small size drinks.

Raita (onion salad) finish the moment we ordered mutton briyani so the restaurant gave me one vegetable. I appreciate it but they should ask me what vegetables I prefer to have, not give any dish they have there.

Ordered food and drinks at 12.33pm. Food arrived in 15 minutes time but the drinks arrived at 1.10pm but this also after we alert them.

Ordered prawn fried rice, oily and covered with many eggs. Egg smell too obvious in the fried rice.

Overall, it's not about paying high price for the food but we need fair portion and tasty food for the price we paying.

Food was generally tasty.
I just wonder why a restaurant will serve beef steak and the beef they serve comes with lots of fats. The chef must be saving the restaurant lots of money by doing so. Ordered some food for new year. Pinoy female Staff was very rude. Horrible service. Female pinoy Staff do not care about customers. Must send them for conmmunication and service course.
As mentioned simply the best choice for sushi people. What to say for the best. Maintained services, good customer service. Keep up the good work. Look forward
Place says Hops&Belly but receipt says Long Jiang Chinos. Nice ambience at night. Quiet and peaceful.

Came to this highly recommended Western food stall in AMK.

Ordered a Chicken Cutlet. Waited for only around 5 mins. Super fast.

The chicken cutlet is huge, probably as big as an adult's face, and it comes with coleslaw, baked beans, French fries and a toast. Have to say that it's very worth the $7 I paid for it.

Nice crunch to the cutlet and its not too dry, just under-seasoned. It made me wished for some gravy or sauce to dip the chicken into.

Overall, not too bad for the price I paid.
One of my go-to places for Indian food. A hot cup of nice teh tarik and crispy prata made to order in this rainy day just‚Ä¶  ü§§üíØ

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Personally felt this place was great, food and staff were amazing. But the killer was the extremely tight spacing between guests, led to space issues and particular group beside me kept looking over when their space felt threatened. Generally just bad environment and experience but food saved it.
The best food and experience here
Staff are friendly. Good place to chill out.

Just had my buffet dinner yesterday with my family.The restaurant was full and the staff explained to us that the food will be slightly slow as there are walk in and events going on.My family decided to wait and surprisingly the staffs were also doing their best to speed up our food.Will definitely support them again with their coming set menu.
Great experience

My children love this place. Service staff are warm and friendly. The food is good and portions are generous. I enjoyed the duck and lychee salad.

So far, all our experiences here have been positive! Def recommend.

Sorry, no pics.... Too busy eating!

Good food at reasonable price. The service is excellent. The white chicken is a must try. We went for dinner for a family of 6 adults and paid $147 inclusive of service charge and GST. Ordered Assam Grouper, white chicken, homemade tofu, salad prawn, prawn ngoh hiang, abalone boiled vegetables. They served the char siew, boiled peanuts and shrimp paste as appetizers. They were tasty, especially the shrimp paste. If you like fatty char siew, it‚Äôs well caramelized and charred but not burnt. We enjoyed the nice ambiance and great service.
The food is authentically Thai but some dishes are overly spicy or sweet. Perhaps this is how it's done just not too suitable for my liking.

Still nice after my last visit 2 years ago.
Always delicious and satisfying!!

Good service and huge variety of food options.

Golden Roll - Good amount of mango, prawn was okay.
Chawanmushi - Average and tastes like how it should be.
Mentaiko Squid - This was really good, generous mentaiko and huge piece of squid!
Hanasaki Ika Tempura - This is the must order whenever at Sushi Tei, crispy and delicious!
Hotate Tamago Udon - Average

Good place to eat with a group of friends given the large menu. Will be back for the Hanasaki Ika Tempura and Mentaiko Squid.

Service is bad. Went at 9AM. Wanted buy Lontong and mee rebus. The lady told the queue was at the other side. Waited at the other queue but ended the same lady served us. Food was horrible. The gravy was too watery. Waste of time

1 masala thosai is 4sgd. Will you buy??? Simply not worth it.
Honest opinion, the food taste for the curries, mutton, and chicken chicken gravy are really good. However when it comes to the goreng stuff, it is tasteless. Basically Overrated and over priced. I do buy their food once or twice a month, as much as I wanted to avoid getting food from there, for some reason... i became helpless at times due to time constraint and it is the only mamak shop available at my area.
They don't have everything which is listed in the menu.
I usually don't dine in, as I stay nearby. But that particularly day I decided to dine in and Ordered the impossible Rogan Josh and a plain thosai. I waited 20mins with the thosai to eat it with the plant base rogan josh. I'm not exaggerating with the timing. I finished my tea waiting for the Rogan josh gravy, I received a plate of impossible roti John 20mins later, And the staff insist that it was what I ordered, then when checked at the cashier, they still kept my order which I wrote with the pencil on the order pad they provided. Found out that the Indian lady (new staff) keyed in my order wrongly, sadly No apologies extended..
A short guy with medium length hair, who i noticed been there with AMK Srisun for long from pre covid, approached. He ask the lady very angrily about the order and shows unhappiness even before I say something.. Honestly I wasn't even complaining when I had to wait 20min for the gravy, but what pisses me off was, when he replied me that they don't have the impossible Rogan Josh With his stern face he asked whether I still want the roti John or not.. I replied him that was not what I ordered..He said ok no problem, and start to process the refund and the lady at cashier keeps apologising to him. I was Worried the new lady staff at cashier would be in trouble for this incident and I told this guy I will just take away that roti John since they already prepared. I asked him to pack it. I also asked Him For some fish curry for my cold thosai. He immediately served it to me. There was no thank You or sorry which is what lacking in these service staff. I remember that I even helped Him by moving myself to another table when he approached me, since there was a big group came later than me, Who needed  the table to be combined.
Anyway this  wasn't the only reason why I end up in Google Review, but It is mainly because I often hear my mum complains that these Srisun workers are very rude.. And sometimes intentionally talking unhappily and sarcastically whenever my mum is there to get her food for work, which is very disturbing while waiting there. She felt intimidated by the way they talk and treat her, I hoping that  something could be done, hope they treat and respect all customers fair and adequately.
food is nice & cheap, this plate cost S$4.80~
Especially waryu beef good quality , highly recommended. Just wish the restaurant can hired more staffs , coz we wait for drink and the food around half hour

I am here at Jack's Place Ang Mo Kio branch to celebrate 2 of my friends' birthday & my own birthday.  The service is really bad here.  The staff are all busy & greeted us with a black face.  There is no service at all & they are charging 10% service charge.  They even charge 50 cents for water.  Very disappointing.

This greedy restaurant has gotten worse ever since they recently removed set meals which costs less.

Main courses and a choice of soup and drink which usually cost total of $14 are now separated. They now charge $8 for soup and $3 for drink.

The new total cost would be $19 for the same exact amount of food.

Even though the food is decent, it's still not worth the price.

Don't come here again and support this place, I certainly won't.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: No unpleasant fishy taste and not bitter at all! So easy to heat up too! Love it helps to boost my body energy and fight fatigue!
Most skewers are good, pork belly skewers are especially awesome!! Ma la xiang guo is pretty good too; they cut the ingredients into bite sizes, very easy to eat.

Its ok only. No cucumber. Rice a bit soft maybe cause I take away. Sambal is sweet not spicy. I dont understand people raving about it. Maybe they never taste a good nasi lemak before. I give it a five out of 10.

Am utterly disappointed with the service I‚Äôve just experience at Ding Tai Feng @ Seletar Mall. I‚Äôm physically queuing outside the restaurant at around 8.20pm but was denied entry by a petite looking lady, informing me that last order by 8.30pm - so left with with disappointment despite seeing a few empty tables just that no one bothers to clear them. But the next moment , I saw her allowing entry for another family. Just don‚Äôt understand ‚Ä¶ last order in 10mins defers between customers. Great disappointment.

Excellent joint, decent enough crowd on a friday night and it was easy to find seats. The meat platter A at $25 with 2 sides was value for money and a good way to try the various meats. I particularly liked the beef brisket and chicken. Sides (mash and ratatouille) were decent and came abit cold but owner kindly helped heat them up. I would say that the platter is probably good for 2 hungry girls but probably a little small for 2 hungry guys. Food came fairly quickly and as a nice touch, the coffee shop also serves beer on tap.
Nice food, ambience (located in a park) and warm service. Definitely one of the top Japanese restaurants in toa payoh/bishan/ang mo kio area

My favourite place to order takeaway butter chicken biryani rice and recently banana leaf nasi lemak. The rice was very fragrant, meat was tender and curry not too spicy. Can order small sides such as stir fried brinjal, ladies fingers, cabbages and dal curry. I wish their naan could be thicker so that there is more bite to it. Their portion is big and price is reasonable. If you're not a bigeater, $10 can buy enough food (without drinks) for 2 people. The male chef and aunties packing the food are always friendly. Will visit this eatery again!

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Interesting and new concoction to bean curd toppings. Not only from usual chin chow or tau sar, you get Kellogg's cereal too
Chicken Chop. I asked for lesser fries more caslaw. Nice portion cheap and good. Be prepared to queue for at least half an hour for your food.
My friends and I loved the quality of the zichar food. Great food and wallet friendly. Remember to try the signature dishes. We will be back again!

Delicious Japanese casual dining in Tai seng.
Good location and easy to find it.
Staff was friendly and food was fresh and yummy!!
Will visit againüëç
Super value for money and authentic Thai food. Had tomyum soup and mango salad. Even though we ordered the smallest sizes, the serving is generous. They are friendly and have great service too.
Great service, owner was friendly and understanding! Food was great, especially the chapati dip (tasted fresh, with a hint of coconut).

I visited this eatery for dinner on a weekend and I must say that it was crowded. So I would advise that you make a reservation first before heading down or you will spend some time waiting. Overall customer service is good, the staff that attended to us was polite and gave good recommendations for the dishes and beverages. Ambiance wise, it was okay, comfortable enough to enjoy your meals. I ordered fresh oysters and they were awesome! A little salty but thick. You have to try it, words cannot tell how good that is. Their meat platter is another. Succulent and grilled to the right texture. Again you have to try it yourself, I really cannot find any words to describe it. Price, is rather affordable in opinion but worth the money.
Decent claypot chicken rice, not much to rave abt. Purchased coupon from shopee at $4.30 as the original price is at $5. Waiting time at least 10 minutes or so during peak hour
Friendly services. Food good.
Good thai food at TPY central , Comfortable place to dine in. Strongly recommended their steam fish with chili lime and grilled pork cheek.

Have to try their Remix Murtabak at SGD6 (with chicken, mutton, sardine inside) but take note different cook have different ingredients, so if you're lucky you get lots of sardine and cheese, which is awesome. Big plate, can share for 2 persons.

The staffs there are friendly and easygoing. Their prata is nice. Recommended for those who have prata cravings especially during midnight because it opens 24 hours daily.

If you're lucky, you may bump into Christopher Lee and Fann Wong with their son having their breakfast there too!

I would give it a 3.5üåü but Google does not have that option.

Location is really good and so is the ambience nice and cozy.

As per attached pictures from the menu they have wines from France, Italy, Slovakia, Australia, Spain and New Zealand.

The selection for Hard Liquor and Cocktails is not extensive though.

Food seems to be fairly priced and very interesting food from Philippines is on the menu.

Service though was certainly not friendly üëé and needs loads of improvement. There was 1 staff however who seemed to be friendly.

For those who sit at the huge Barrel (drums) kindly note ‚ö†Ô∏è , they have wheels and may roll  down the slope, you got to be cautious as drinks may spill over in the direction of the slope.

The restaurant seems to have a steady stream of customers.

It's a good idea to check with the restaurant on their food and drinks promo.

Since seating inside the restaurant is limited you may want to call the restaurant in advance and make reservations.

Real awesome Indian comfort food! Definitely one of my new favourite Indian restaurants! Great flavour with just the right kick of spiciness. Must try the mutton briyani...damn happening! Highly recommend!
Food here was decent. Staff is friendly. Serving is fast.

Never going to order from here again and i advise others not to as well unless you rly nothing better to do. Waited close to 1hr for delivery food and yet still preparing. Not the first time as well. Had to head down personally to see whats the situation and found out so many riders waiting for orders. Poor kitchen management. DTF or paradise dynasty better than this
Guys, just to update u 8.50 for chicken cutlet ya. So yup, not going back lol. Also cheapo auntie give 2 package chilli some more tell me i put the chilli inside alr ah haha. GL.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: A place to go for Korean food! Pancake is especially nice.

Food is nice with reasonable price, GST inclusive. Authentic Malaysian Food. Like their curry Chu Cheong Fun and Char Siew in the dry noodles. The Char Siew just tasted like those I had in Malaysia. Yam cake is good too.

Go elsewhere for better food!! Better close ur restaurant than to hire such staffs!
Had their food twice! Food mediocre. Super Attitude- Service terrible . All waitresses busy looking at their handphones. Not interested to serve you and will argue , raise voice at you. We were the only customers in the restaurant at 5:15pm. Takeaway chicken curry taste terrible. Not worth paying the price to dine in or takeaway.  The place doesn‚Äôt have aircon. Super humid even with fan. Need to pay extra $0.50 for takeaway box. I give 1star for your chilli sauce!

Tasty nasi padang worth a try if u‚Äôre in the area. However prices have been creeping up like with many other places...

$6.90 for one meat two veg now. Additional 30cents for beef/seafood.

good food as cheap as hawker centre, tried most of the food stalls here and all are pretty good and worth the try! the longan drink at the entrance really quenches the thirst and one of my fav here would be the chaykeowtiao and hokkienmee!
Serving time is a little slow but the food are better than my expectation.

Food at Yalong Zhicar is nice. Good to go in group of 4 - 6 pax to share their La la Hor Fun. Those who like La la should try this because they are generous with the la la . They also have 'Fire' Chicken ...very unique way of eating, should try this also but need to order 1 day in advance. This place is crowded at night even on a weekday night.
Very good service and unique dishes. Spicy diced chicken Ëæ£Â≠êÈõû and water boiled fish Ê∞¥ÁÖÆÈ≠ö are a must!!

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: It‚Äôs a nice hawker centre in Toa Payoh, tried the lei cha and the soya milk, really worth the price.

Chose a chinese restaurant for our National Day dinner!

Has been recommended to this restaurant by many of my friends, we reach there early to make sure we can secure a parking space.

Yellow Pot at Duxton Reserve

We were very impressed with the Decor, I would categorised it as the Oriental Black Style but immediately after we settle down, we were disturbed by a group of Chinese Boys (tourist), tons of vulgarities and loud noise diffuse throughout the restaurant. Disappointed at their behaviour at such a classy and exquisite restaurant. Almost destroyed our dinning experience.

Let‚Äôs talk about the food.

We were informed that the food will take a bit of time to prepare and our first dish came out after 30 mins. But we were not disappointed with the food quality, the appetizer was Fried Prawns with Sesame Mayo, the big and crunchy prawn with the well-balanced Mayo sauce was a perfect match. This is follow by 2 soups, Double Boiled Chicken Soup and Crabmeat and Fish Maw. My wife love the crabmeat and fishmaw as it taste similar to her favourite sour-spicy soup. The chicken soup was great too, it comes with an abalone and it sure has been cooking for hours to attain this level of flavour.

The 2 mains we ordered were the Signature Roasted Duck and Fermented Red Wine Yeast Chilean Seabass. The duck was the purpose of this trip and it does not disappoint, crunchy and thin skin pair with the soft and savoury meat, simplify delightful. My wife love the seabass, it is a very small portion and quite salty therefore I would recommend that you pair the fish with some rice.

We also ordered the Freshly Peeled Crabmeat Fried Rice, with the price, I was expecting more crab meat but nonetheless, it taste awesome. You can eat the fried rice just on its own (without any side dishes).

Our dessert, Crispy Pancake with Red Bean Fillings, to my wife surprise, this was the best dish of the day. It looks ordinary but once you put a piece into your mouth, you will stop at nothing to eat the whole plate. It was that good! A Must Try

Rating: 8.5/10

If you are hungry for awesome chinese food with an amazing decor, look no further.

#duxton #duxtonreserve #yellowpot #chinese #oriental #crab #duck #soup #abalone #redbeanpaste #seabass #seafood #prawn #fishmaw #simonlew #simonreview #foodreview #nationalday #sg #dinner

Based on the hardwarezone forum, came across this newly opened ramen outlet located in a coffee shop @ Toa Payoh-Braddell area. Ordered the Tonkotsu Ramen with Special toppings. Soup taste was excellent, with great collagen base in it. Ramen wise, the noodle is kinda thin, but does not lack the Q element in it, in fact it swallows rather smoothly, definitely great addition for kids and elderly. The aijitama (flavoured egg) have excellent colouring in it, which is surprising for non restaurant style ramen shop. The chasyu however is abit salty, but i guess is rather important for the broth. Taste similar to Keisuke Ramen. Overall, price is cheap and the quality is excellent. Definitely, a place to go if you prefer no queue, fast, tasty and a affordable ramen dining experience.
held our tea ceremony and luncheon banquet over here, excellent service and food is awesome!!

Used to patronise this place because food was good. Today's dinner us a disappointment.  The chicken is not tender and meaty like it used to be. Understand because of inflation everything is expensive. But for the price paid for this standard of food I think its not worth. Many hawker stalls now serve tastier chicken rice.
their samsui chicken still as good and quite a Q to wait during dinner time.

Affordable and good western food. This place is a bang for your buck. Highly recommended.

<EDIT> 20220520 - have dropped my rating of JWS Grille factory. standard has dropped. ordered a ribeye, but they served a sirloin. very disappointed.
Great prata..great curry..great sambal..you add together it becomes super dahüëç

We were there last monday during lunch. Ordered and waited for close to 30mins. I had to enquire before they realise that they forgot to key in our orders (drinks were served btw). It was not a great experience as throughout the time we waited, nobody checked on us even though the place was not busy. We had to takeaway in the end as we were already late.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Never gets disappointed when having meals in this place. The soy sauce chicken is one of the best in Singapore. The hainan rice is delicious
One of the go to place after your morning walk around Thomson reserve. Prata and curry are okay. Like the outdoor seating as it isn't so hot and stuffy.
Always the curry fish head,  the taste of the gravy is so perfect though the fish head is  abit small but veg inside is generous üëå üíØ

Tucked in a corner of a HDB estate and came across quaint. The whole steamed fish with lime sauce was excellent and the rest of the food were not too bad. What made the dining experience unpleasant was being barked at by the waitress to put the empty gong shells back on our plates if we were done when 1) she could have asked nicely 2) provided an empty plate for the shells. Also it was excruciatingly painful to ask for a second serving of white rice which never arrived. I‚Äôve never been in such a hurry to leave a food establishment. The steamed fish could never make up for the appalling attitude of that waitress.

We were stuck at Toa Payoh Industrial Park due to sudden heavy rain so decided to have dinner at nearby coffeeshop. Surprised by the many stalls still open at this hour in this area; we decided to have mookata since perfect weather to eat something hot. Wow!!! No regrets! Not only the seafood was fresh, everything was tasty. More importantly, I don't feel thirsty. Best experience was the stall owner cook and guide us when I asked him how and what I should cook first as I've never tried mookata. Despite the heavy rain, it was a perfect evening with great discovery, yummy Mookata Lor!!! I will definitely be back again. üòã

Absolute chaos upon opening time. Queue up for 1 hour+ to the end only to get a queue number that is estimated to be 3 hours or even longer, by the time it becomes dinner alr.üòÇ quite a number of people ragequitted. Could have just blanket cutoff the queue and not make everybody waste time queueing further. Probably will give this a miss.

Delicious authentic Shanghainese food in a small family business tucked away at a quiet corner in amk. The XLB is comparable or even better than DTF's. The chef takes pride in his food and does not allow customers to takeaway food which will not taste as good if taken out. Advisable to call to book before visiting as the restaurant only has ard 6 tables.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: had my fav fishball noodle in the morning.. plenty of good food for breakfast to start the day.
Amazing tasting food, creatively done for a nice twist on traditional Chinese dishes. Reasonable prices as well for CBD.
I had the Fragrance Bee Hoon with gravy. It brings back memories of the old school taste. Nostalgic

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Food is good but sad they took out Snapple now. Side can be better. Side dish standard drop compare to last time.

Brought my family here on a quiet Monday afternoon. Place was as expected not crowded. Ordered the yellow chieve hor fan ($12) and hot plate tofu . Oh mine, was pretty speechless. The hor fan had no ingredients at all! Only bean sprout. The tou fu was so pathetic, that even the egg layer that comes with hot plate, was so paper thinly spread, that I suspect they barely used half an egg on it. For a moment, I thought I has ordered paper prata.

I am pretty sure this will be my last visit to this place. I had came before few years ago, and it wasn't this terrible to my memory. Perhaps the management had changed ü§î

The only saving grace to this place, is the lack of crowd, and the aircon üòÄ
After I read online that this uncle from 711 S-11 opened stall here. I've always wanted to try it for myself. This smell .. this taste... Brings back memories! The coffee a bit meh though...

The queue speaks for itself, extensive menu of quality sushi, though slightly pricey.

Full fledged restaurant with ramen and don offerings in their menu, atop the usual sushi and sashimi, not to mention their kids meal which is served in a different plate and presentation!

They also have a unique way of serving their dishes, whereby customers places their order via an online platform found on a QR code, and is served by a robotics train system, a truly good fit for COVID period.

Will definitely return in future given the wide selection and fair price point üëçüèª
Like the prata & tosai.  Not so oily.

Overall above average. Good food, reasonable price, lots of parking, walking distance from amk mrt. But crowded place and long waiting time. It‚Äôs better to make reservation by calling them if your group is more than 4. Will come back for this.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Small selection but value for money
The food is quite nice, especially the Thai milk tea
One of my fav Penang style yuenyang (lor mee + prawn mee) ! Standard has been consistent over the past 10 years

Tonkotsu Specialüçúüç•

üçú Food wise: Egg is good, mouthful, watery and well seasoned. Ramen is quite Q. Cha shu, not too bad. Big Nori sheet. This bowl might not be suitable for me though, might need to give it another go for other flavours! But do give it a try!

‚ú® Ambience wise: Coffeeshop

ü§µüèª Service wise: Staff friendly

üíµ Price wise: $10.90 for this bowl

They used to be very good but no longer good.
2 weeks ago we went there(since Covid started, we never been there), the standard of pan-fried dumplings (ÈîÖË¥¥) has drop, very disappointed; noodles (ÁÇ∏ÈÖ±Èù¢) and Â∞èÁ¨ºÂåÖ ‚Ä¶
Ambience old school. Staff friendly food is good .. they have this sea bass only $12.80

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Staff rude attitude, poor service & unfriendliness. We had 9 pax dining in, however they refuse to use the larger table top despite the cramp small table and further giving ridiculous reasons. For the sake of your dining experience, dont consider dining here!
Ginger pork belly with onsen egg  taste average and cos $5.50 is definitely value for money!

Our favourite private dining restaurant. Great service & good food. We love the signature Yu Sheng, the Kagoshima Wagyu beef, the Tomatoes in wasabi sesame sauce & the Angel Hair tofu soup. Also try the Truffle Chicken, the seafood white bee hoon & the Pregnant woman's fried rice. Delicious! Great selection of wine & whiskey.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Bad experience. Went there on the 3rd day of CNY. Ordered a soup, vegetable, bean curd, pork belly, lala. The bill came up to 200++. Food quality was bad. Ordered a takeaway fried rice - costs $18. ‚Ä¶

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content:
Nice experience, walked in randomly for dinner.
Menu items are all indian dishes. Ample and spacious seating observed. Staffs very warm and friendly. Ordered briyani and meat dishes. Food was served fast and warm. Meat were fresh and very tender. Wouldn't mind visiting again. üòÉ
Nice food with reasonable price.

Expensive but tasteless, low quality food.
Stir fried carrot cake with xo sauce- just deep fried carrot cake, while the egg and bean sprouts were cooked separately, then placed together.
E-fu noodles was terrible as well. $15.80 for noodles with mushroom and a few pcs of spring onion. No meat whatsoever. Tasteless too. Feel so cheated.
Will definitely not return.
Nice and cool

Not anywhere close to a decent chinese restaurant.

I have to say this is one place, that might not be worth your time. Peking duck was not restaurant standard the duck skins that was wrapped were dry and seem like it was kept for sometime.

The other dishes were also just normal. No wow factor and lacked the taste and wok hey.

Very very very good fried rice, chilli and pork üòã Novena is quite far for me but I will come back just for this!

*Shoutout to Shinjin for recommending this

Recently ordered their fish and chip and grilled fish to try. Well I am quite impressed and it was quite good especially the grill fish that it was cooked well and has flavor with the brown sauce. Fish and chip is typical but both portion size may be small doe most people.

Ordered chicken spaghetti with cream sauce and spring chicken whole to try. The spaghetti noodle was well cook not too soft, chicken is bland like poach in water and throw into the spaghetti to cook. The cream sauce lacks flavor and not rich, a bit running. However the chicken was good, loved their crispy skin that is packed with flavours and not oily. Worth trying their fried spring chicken!

Good old school Western food, waiting time can be easily 30 mins or more during peak hour, but the lady boss will always inform you about the estimated timing, if u can't wait, you can always try others food and somewhere else. Dine-in, they still serve the food to you instead of self service.

Best prata, I love it. Awesome curry and crunchy fresh prata.
Edit: years later and still my No. 1 in Singapore :)

Most of the item I would like to have was not available. The sashimi was presented like a bento set which I don‚Äôt know how to appreciate most important of all not fresh. The chicken was big in portion but not well marinated. The only consolation was the tempura prawn manage to meet the bar. Sake selection was bad very limited . Even the light soya sauce also taste funny and dark in colour . Staff was friendly. Overall dun worth the money.

We went at around 1+pm and our last order is at 145pm for the dim sums as we need to vacate out by 2.30pm so that they can prepare for the 3pm buffet dim sum.

Food is good, except for the egg tart that is not those that don't have many crispy layers,  chicken feet is nice but can be softer,  I feel that they did not cook long enough, as for the rest of the dishes are good,  spring roll are crispy,  deep fried wanton is nice,  carrot cake with xo sauce,  century egg porridge,  fried prawn with mango also very nice.  I don't really like their chee cheong fan as the cha siew got a little bit of the pork smell which I'm scare of.  The cha siew bao is nice,  the lotus rice is nice too.  If you love to eat dim sum at a reasonable price,  you can come here or other outlets to try it out.  Service is fast and food serving is fast too.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: The rice was well cooked and fragrant, the star of the show is of course the chicken. Nicely charred and tender, coupled with their house made chilli (pleasurable burn). Ikan bilis was just a tad too salty for my liking. I would come back just for their chicken üëçüèº

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
Meat is good, would recommend going coffeeshop serves beer on tap too
Ordered the 2 person platter for 22
Great food & good service. Not too oily and love their not too sweet tea too.

Had a very bad experience today because of the incompetence of the service lady. I wanted to order large Lor Mee to ensure that it is enough for my family of 4 and asked if large is sufficient. The lady then advice me to go for medium if I am afraid we cannot finish. I then point to the menu and ask for the price of medium since I only see regular and large. The lady then assured me there is a medium but could not tell me the price even when I probed.

After a pointless exchange, we decided on large and thought that it means the large on the menu ($20+). When we were served, we were surprise that the standard pot was not big enough and our order came in 2 pots. At this point, I still did not sense anything wrong as I seldom dine in Putien and thought this is normal practice for large size Lor Mee.

It was only when I made payment that I realised the order was extra large and the price is not even stated on menu. I was so angry as I clearly wanted large. However it was too late since we already consumed the food and even take away the leftovers.

At the same time, we attempted to cancel a drink that we ordered but was not yet served. However, we were taken aback by the rude reaction from one of the service lady and her refusal to help us cancel the order. I have to compliment the male manager who intervened and help us cancel the order after he overheard the conversation.

I really did not expect such an experience and find this unacceptable for an established restaurant. Very disappointing.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Here for the braised pork rice which did not disappoint.

Came here using the Great Eastern rewards 1-1 special promo for my birthday month and it was truly a happy experience. Slipper lobster and pasta is really yummy!! The hulk mocktail (taste like green apple) was very fragrant and refreshing as well‚Ä¶ The staffs (sharlene, etc) here were friendly and wide food selection to choose from. There‚Äôs a clean washroom in their restaurant.. We also ordered using 1-1 (2-5pm) promo from Jack‚Äôs place fish&chips and steak&chicken combo. Overall it was a nice place to chill and dine, will be back again!

Not my 1st unhappy experience..... I dun blame the staff coz I got the same answer thrice. Among so many Japanese bento brand, tis is the only one very stingy with sauce.

At Wadori, each time I asked for more sauce, staff sure say "it's gonna be very salty ya". The initial dri≈º≈ºle of sauce is so insignificant, how salty can it be? (I'm not exaggerating, it's really miserable)

Then they will highlight "additional sauce will cost additional 70cents".
70cents for another miserable drizzle of sauce?

I hope u can improve on tis, dun make ur staff say the same sentences again, do something abt the sauce. If not, u can consider giving way to other brands.

p.s. tdy's rice is mushy, not the usual Japanese rice standard.
Such a shame that I just found out this restaurant recently. The food was so good that you cannot tell there‚Äôs no meat at all. Mala grilled fish is the must and dim sum at lunch must try also!!!
I had the Sirloin steak for 9.90 anniversary promotion, very tender and juicy beef.

This is a small family restaurant with 3 staff only. Always make reservation before you head to the restaurant as there are limited seats. A cozy place where you can get authentic Shanghainese foods. We recommend fried bun ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖ and spring roll Êò•Âç∑.
Had the rib-eye steak and the signature. Loved the sour cream baked potato. Beef was hot and not too bad for medium well. Expect to wait a little during peak hour.
Food quality and service standard has dropped. Price has gone up. Tea charged by no. of persons, although the serving size is the same - one pot regardless of head count (add water only).
Needing a nasi lemak fix and thinking of Sedap once more!
Nice food chain Hotel...

I was there on 28th June 2022 to try the new teppanyaki store that replaced express teppanyaki. It was dinner time and as usual crowded. I was seated behind the first counter and a few more customers came after me.  I do not expect any service as it's not fine dining. As I was waiting I noticed the cook (won't call him a chef cooking for the customers who came after me. The young boy noticed that I was not being served and told his colleague to cook mine as I came first. He told the young boy not to bother about me while he's cooking for other customers. I also noticed that instead of cooking based on sequence, he pick and choose which one he wants to cook first. I asked for a refund and the boy mending the cashier was nice enough to give me the refund. Having said this, of course I did not taste the food because I've already lost my appetite. Never experienced this when I dine with other teppanyaki stores.
Food tasty
The food is very good but the price is a little high. I know it‚Äôs because they use top quality ingredients. In a restaurant you‚Äôd pay that price. We go there once a month.
V nice. Hope they can maintain their standards of yummy good good food.

Brought my dad here for dinner on a Saturday night.

Waitress was a chinese auntie (possibly lady boss) gave us one menu and stood beside us right away, expecting us to quick fire our orders to her. Asked for some time to look thru the menu as it was my first time visiting. She literally walked one round the restaurant (30 secs), and came back standing beside my table again.

While I was translating the English menu to my dad, she kept interrupting and suggested us to order the dishes she recommended. My dad got pretty annoyed and said to dine at another place instead. I returned the menu to her and apologized for the trouble, but she just rolled her eyes and did not even acknowledge me. Dodged a bullet and definitely not dining here ever.
Reasonably priced bentos
mala here is not too bad, is quite fragrant. price used to be decent, i believe there is price increment recently as its slightly more expensive than when i ate here a year ago.
Fxxking good pratas. I rate the best in the AMK neighborhood. Their goreng items on point too.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Like the vibrance.
Food is great, price affordable just that the staffs nonchalant attitude .. Talking among themselves until you raised your voice.

Probably the closest to Malaysian style dry noodles you can get in Singapore, although not there yet.....but just. I think if it had a bit more dark soya sauce then it will be perfect. Their noodles are also Malaysian style too. Portions are very generous and noodles were packed with flavours from the dark soya sauce and pork lard. Prepare to queue at least 30 minutes on a weekend morning.

Ichiban Boshi have good lunch deals and the food is alright. However if without lunch promotion the price of the food would be quite pricey and i would suggest eating something else. There are better food around Jurong Point
The staff attitude there is very bad.especially the malaysian workers.i will not go back there again.they were rude to me

Garlic bread is amazing, perfect.
Calamansi as well - go-to on a hot sweltering day! Their mains are great, love the variety of pastas to choose from.

I've heard good things about this place for many years but today my first time there it wasn't that great... Menu is very limited and prices are acceptable but noodle portions could be bigger. Xiao long bao is shanghai style, the skin is thick.

rly affordable and delicious thai food!! pad thai was amazing as well as the whole fish! green curry and tom kha were good as well with lots of sauce!! highly recommend you order those with rice :-)

only thing is that the curry and soups are typically quite thin and doesn‚Äôt have lots of ingredients in them. i think that‚Äôs alright because the price is already so affordable anyway but just to keep in mind when deciding on portions!!

pick up was smooth and rly quick as well :-) thank u for the good meal

Operated by a couple, serving lunch, not noticeable at this canteen, located near Eunos Industrial.
Ordered for a portion for 2 ÁÉßËÖäÈ∏°È•≠„ÄÅreasonable at $10.

Dum briyanis are awesome.
Chicken is moderate
Mutton is hot
Chicken dum briyani must try
The food was great! Must try the Naan bread.

Extremely good service! The food selection is quite huge as well, their donburis are really good and the portions are reasonably big, as well as their skewers, highly recommended to try them.

The prices are a bit on the expensive side, but that's the standard of such restaurants, I think it's worth a try if you're willing to spend a bit.
Went there for chinese new year and the food was excellent. Especially the carb noodles. The pork was crispy and tender
Finally found where you've relocated too! Missed your power mee rebus for years! Am very happy and satisfied now.  Standard still the same. Yum-yum !!! Will be back for more !
Third time coming to this outlet. Good place for large gathering if book ahead. Mains portion is very large. In-house cakes and dessert is the best.
The lunchtime 3-course meal is nice and affordable. The meats are on the more expensive side, but the main dishes are pretty good and fairly priced. The atmosphere was very relaxing and chill.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: I just ordered basil pork with egg through grab  but it come without egg. Zzzz.
Rarely listens to my request for no pickles

I find this place good and cheap.
Order the truffle Ramen the taste not that much of truffle but it's smell incredible for that price below 10 leh.
And the karage also combo with drinks.
It's cheap and also very delicious at the price of such.
Highly recommend it!
The place also seating now due to covid.

Here for brunch and dinner before. The otah bruschetta with grilled cheese is a must. Dinner menu is so-so, portion can be bigger even though the food is good. Love the place as it allowed furkid to accompany the hoomans under shelter. Nice cafe in a quiet estate.
Nice neighborhood thai restaurant. Decent green curry chicken and minced pork basil. Payaya salad was terrible - overdosed on fish sauce.
Good affordable Thai food. I would give it a 5 if 7 didn't find it a bit too salty. The Tom yam was slightly more sour than usual.
Don't like the taste of the foods.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Food is okay but service is average (maybe business is too good). The restaurant missed my reservation. I learned upon arrival (I have called in 3 weeks before). They then made arrangement for empty hall area at level 2 for lunch.

During this point of time the max number is 5 pax allowed per table and amazingly their set lunch menu only have 4 or 6 pax (maybe they dont care or can't be bothered).

I feel there are better choices out there and will skip this place for lunch next time.

Dim sum is good, we like the dim sum, but some suggestion:
1) should have tea pot tea instead of tea in a cup, Chinese È£≤Ëå∂ style.
2) please cheer up your waitress, they look in bad mood, when serve should say please enjoy and when we say thank you they should say you are welcome . Basic manners must apply! I wish you all the best. I guarantee your business will be much better if you can improve dinning services.
Yummy but no napkins and quite pricey. Not a lot of meat in the bryani.

The wedding venue was clean and spacious. It was not bad. We eventually chose to go with Qian Xi but i had a very bad experience with Torrance.

Torrance was really disrespectful throughout the conversation for discussion of prices, number of tables and so and so. Torrance paid no heed to me and talked over me when i am asking questions about the banquet. He looked at my husband the entire time and it was like i didn‚Äôt exist the entire time. I felt really horrible because it was supposed to be a gathered discussion, it seemed like my opinion did not matter. My husband even tried to include me but Torrance would just ignore me. Really really horrible experience. But because of time constraints we had no choice but to go with Qian Xi.

Thankfully, Owen was really helpful throughout the entire experience and provided lots of assurance and insights about the flow etc. Feedbacks during the food tasting was taken into consideration and food was really good during the banquet itself! Staff service was good as well!

Anyways, we had feedback to some of our friends about Torrance and they seem to have similarly bad experience. Beware of this Torrance dude cause he might just ruin your day.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Nice food... reasonable price... good customer service.. recommend mutton chukka....
Food taste great, service by Theva and the team are fantastic even they are very busy. They fulfilled all our requests!
The pork was quite dry for the curry don, the hotpot was alright and quite a huge portion, can be shared by 2 persons.
SUPER BAD customer service. Ignore you all the way till you ask them able to take order and is during off peak hours.
Delicious reasonably priced fresh Japanese food in the heartlands. It would be advisable to reserve a place as it is well patronised. 10% discount during Happy hour (5.30 pm to 7pm).

Ordered Udon and Skewers. The hottest thing were the Miso Soup and Chawamushi, the others are all lukewarm. Lukewarm Udon!

If you have to eat here, avoid these two.

Easy parking space at the back of coffee-shop. Have had better Nasi Padang elsewhere. Rice was clumpy. Vegetable dish, terong (brinjal) sambal balado, was cold. Rendang was good though a tad salty & the kerisik (fried grated coconut) had a bit burnt taste. Taste is subjective thus I urge Google Map users to try this place, at least once! You might like it better than I did. ;-)
Fried tomato egg is well done. However, the lamb skewer was undercooked. Skewer meat is also very fatty.
Like their traditional Hakka food and the place is very cosy
Opening hours till 10pm... But stop customers from entering at 830pm.. alrighty
Amazing food.. staff shown great attitude towards customers.. when we entered the restaurant we had few doubts. First sip of soup chaged our perceptive.. must visit place.. nice service by staff..

Tried signature chicken chop. Rich taste of sweet and sour with a bit of peppery sauce. Chicken thigh meat was juicy and tender. Old school coleslaw and fries. For the portion, you got the value for money.
The food was so good.. Forgot to take photos üòÇ. Reasonably priced good food and desserts!

Second time here..
Food was good especially their marmite ribs and tofu (silky smooth).

Will definitely return to try other dishes.

Slightly overpriced.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: I went today. Foods are amazing . Service too good
Would recommend the char siew wonton noodles from this shop! The dumplings are also well filled.

Location is relatively convenient. The restaurant(the setting is actually a canteen in the day and restaurant by night) occupancy rate was ~70% during my visit. Reckon the food was slightly above average but the bill was HIGHLY about average (you probably would prefer a better setting, in air conditioned environment with the price you paid). Parking is always an issue over there... so,  go early if you need a slot. As for the waitresses... not that friendly if i may compare against my previous patronage. Generally, still an OK place to go for.
Food and services good. Especially their fried Salmon fish head soup which always finish very fast. Hope they can have more on the menu for the day cos usually it's sold out by lunch

Today I have mutton rice asked worker to put little extra piece. They charged $ 11.50 price. Which is ridiculous for the meal. They gave only curry apart one vegetable which is smelly and useless appalam. I mean not puffy. When I asked why are you charging this much simple answer for the extra piece. Day light robbery. When I asked for the break up they literally showing finger. Just pay or keep the food you ate.
Friendly staff. Meal was decent. Chilli crab pasta was spicy and for the more adventurous taste buds.
Nice food at very reasonable price! No wonder it's often very crowded during lunch hour.  The curry chicken is a must try.

Eat at your own risk. I‚Äôm not sure what‚Äôs the rave‚Äôs about. Bill was $42, if you wan to Taobao, they charge a hefty 50cents+get.   :( service was good as they noticed we had kids and required fork and spoon and scissors. Food was not nice though. The sweet and sour pork was so so and the veggies were not cooked. The jjm was very salty and not much ingredients. Seafood food had a measly 2 pieces of squid as seafood, not even fake crabmeat or frozen shrimp. Everything was just full of onions. Lastly is the side dishes, only kimchi, nothing else. Me and hubs got diarrhoea and vomiting after eating here. Sad

They told me our orders would take about 20-25 minutes. I waited mine for 45 minutes. I cancelled my order in the end. My 3 fellow diners had their food arrived 10 to 15 minutes one after another. By the time they finished all their food, mine has arrived. In the end I cancelled my order.
Female Staff likely the manger was energetic, food was freshly made. Great customer service.
Not a good experience in this banquet. waitress keep ask us to push chair in. refilling drinks - a waitress pour water into sprite. tea into beer. serving food in a attitudes manner.

È£üÁâ©Â•ΩÂêÉÂà∞......‰ª§‰∫∫ÊµÅÊ≥™„ÄÇOrdered crab bee hoon. Crab was ultra fresh and super sweet. Shell was cracked perfectly so eating is a breeze. Bee hoon is quality so it remains tangy till the end. Soup taste so good that makes my last day of 2019 so touching.... Please keep up the standard. Will be back.

Liked the mushroom soup, and ribeye with merlot sauce. BBQ ribs was fall-off-the -bone tender. Battered fish n chips is a bit soggy, tho well flavoured. Huge serving of curly fries; but taste like the frozen type.
Big portion ,nice
Amazing briyani. I am completely taken by surprise. This is the closest India Indian food I can find in Singapore. Friends from southern India will love this place.

What the hell is this? Ordered Klang Bak Kut Teh and Sesame chicken at Northpoint, took more than 25 mins to be served and at the end no taste of the Bak Kut Teh, meat hard, so much different from the picture and the sesame chicken was too salty, taste of no sesame oil. Lastly, do look at the photos and comment. Seriously, it's worst than other branches that I have.
Quite expensive, food were good. Service is bad. Server don't care much on service and 10% service charge.

Brunch at Malaysia Boleh@AMK Hub.
Highlight is the: KL Curry Yong Tau Fu Chee Cheng Foo ÂêâÈöÜÂù°ÂíñÂñ±Á≤ÆË±ÜËÖêÁå™ËÇ†Á≤â.
$5 (2 persons to share as we bought other food, too): CCF, brinjal, dry bean curd, wanton, sausage, curry sauce n a sprinkle of sesame seeds.
Great breakfast at Malaysia Boleh.
Please come later, like around afternoon for: FKT, KL hokkien mee, Hainansese chicken rice and many more.

Any food labelled KL, Penang, Malacca, Ipoh‚Ä¶ I w eat. Missing these cities n the people very much.

After all the fuss about how good their prata is, we decided to pay a visit. Crispy yes, but is it that nice? Nope. Paying $2.40 for 1 egg prata is not worth it, plus it was super oily. As for the maggi goreng chicken, paying $6.60 for some simple tossed noodles is ridiculous. I would give $3.50 max. Finding the parking space was another headache. Maybe my fellow Singaporeans want an aircon place to relax and chit chat. Even that should be avoided since it is covid times. Conclusion, just not worth it. Ask me and I can suggest other neighbourhood uncles selling superb tasting pratas and maggi goreng.

Hi everyone, I am shirley, the daughter of the cook of vincent western food. My mom is the auntie taking order. Recently, just this year two of my parent's long term employee are no longer working for us (>20 years). Vincent western food is lacking manpower and it has been difficult to find employees and my parents are very stressed and tired with the workload. If you have any one that wishes to work, please direct them to me and contact me at 96575643. PLS let vincent western food continue! If we are still unable to find employee, my parents will handle the stall themselves which mean longer wait time and possibly shorter opening hours due to old age. we seek your kind undertstanding.

First time at a Collin's, always been intrigued by their dry aging fridge, so decided to give it a try. Ordered the US  Mishima Wagyu ribeye steak (MS5, 250gm) and carbonara. I think they were doing pretty ok with their offering, till I get to the over cooked part of the steak - which was thinly sliced in the first place - making it pretty hard to sear and control doneness. Still very decent I think.

This bowl at $6.90 is one of the cheapest good quality ramen I‚Äôve tasted. It‚Äôs not overly salty like other ramen (if you like more salty you can let them know). The broth is not those super thick but thick enough to be flavourful. Tabao the gyoza home and it was very good too.

Highly recommended for its great price and qualify
Though the staff was friendly, the food n ingredients were fresh n well cooked but I personally think has too much MSG. If they can make the aftertaste less salty, it will be great
Pricey... But nothing to eat at lunch.. weird place...
One of my favorite restaurants in Singapore!!  Good quality food with the same Indian taste!

Food is good and price is reasonable, don't compared the soup with beauty pot. Individual liking.  2A2C, The staff told me I have to order additional pot for my kids but I saw other table come in later than me order 3 pots share by 6 Adults. I did not question the staff, I will order 2 pots next times instead of each per pot

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Handmade dim sum
Do not sell special braised chicken feet
SALTED EGG SAUCE IS TERRIBLE, FULL OF FLOUR.
Very satisfied with the seasonal meatless menu!! Generous portion! Delish!

Good airconditioned zi char place. We had the set for 10. It included the lobster porridge in claypot with the lobster served separately (a very tasty and yummy one), cabbage chicken in claypot, steam grouper Hong Kong style, scallops with broccoli, tofu with enoki mushrooms and puay ling vegetables, smoked duck with jellyfish, braised abalone with mushrooms and sea cucumber, and orh ni for dessert. I didn't eat the abalone dish as it came out just before the dessert and I was way too full for it. Should have served the dish earlier. My 2 favourites were the lobster porridge and the tofu dish. Price was reasonable, service was great. Very attentive service staff. The place was clean but could have been more comfortable if the air-con was functioning properly.

Newly open coffeeshop with many interesting shops. Tried this Japanese stall which has many branches. The curry sauce is think and flavourful, but the rice is a little lumpy and katsu was a little oily. Overall still worth to try since it is below $10 üëçüèº Hope they will improve the katsu.
Love the food here is clean and hygienic!

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: the anchorvale outlet is good. happy with the taste and portion.
The char kuay teow is a must try!

$8 is pretty value for money as you can add 2 sides.
I had the curry don. The curry was a little less unfortunately, but the meat was thick and tasty.
Will return for more.
Nice food

Cheaper than other ‚Äútrain‚Äù sushi places but you can taste the subpar quality as well.

Take something you like and make it better, not worse.

Ordered Chicken Katsu w/ Curry Sauce Donburi.

Katsu: Quite nice
Curry: Decent
Rice: Decent
Price: A bit on the high side

A surprising find, located in a nondescript 2nd floor. We ordered one of the set lunches which represents good value. Their signature Chicken claypot was soft to the bone which was flavoursome. Carrot cake had a slight crisp, Steamed gourd with fish was moist, I wish they sliced the cuttlefish thinner for ease of enjoyment. Tofu was also cooked perfectly.
Siew Mai, Thickened soup and Braised pork rib were pedestrian
Overall the dishes were well executed and homey in taste. The dining room had a poor acoustic effects so it is annoying during peak period.

Food is tasty and the price is very reasonable. Got enough variety for most guys to come here around 3 times a week. They got Briyani, prata fried Malay food and their outlets are all halal. The restaurant is clean and their service is decent. Would've given it 4 stars if the toilet was cleaner/in better quality and had toilet rolls.
Poori sucks
Great staff and live band and atmosphere and quality of wine and food and price.

Serves a wide selection of local zi char stall dishes. There are several popular items which are not shown on the menu. Taste is great overall and so is the pricing for majority of the dishes. Prices of those seasonal dishes like crab etc, tends to be higher.
Worst place...service totally out....we ask one they give one
I like the sambal fried kway teow, the taste is good... But the taste for rest of the dishes not as good as expected...

Cheap and good prata, air conditioned seating too.

Must order - mutton murtabak!

We tried the outlet at Novena and was disappointed with the food served except for the cold dish appetite, pork slices which is surprisingly tender and the sauce combines well with meat. The beef rendang was tough and the tofu kai lan was salty. Rice was not properly cooked as well. They appeared to be short of staff, and food takes quite a while to be served. The seating area is quite cramped as well.
Good environment, good n fast service,  reasonably priced, good food... 5*
Found a nice new cafe. Great food, pet friendly and can cycle over the next round. Just a bit longer waiting time for a seat so better to book advance ü•Ç

They don't serve thosai at any time of the day, only briyani, naan, rice sets. No prata either.

Vegetarian rice set - the ingredients were little and the vadai was small. I could get something similar for less than half the price outside. Would go to komala villa nearby instead.

Service was fine.
I love their food and ambience. Reasonable price. Friendly owners. Pls reserve table before going. Bring along friends and family.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Very good place for a hassle free drinks and food. Their chilli chicken and biryani tastes very nice. Would definitely visit again.
I have been eating their western food since10 year old at clementi 308. Now I'm 40

Love the pan fried mixed seafood & pork dumpling. New love for boiled version recently, hethier choice yet remain tasty with the freshness subtlely mixing in your mouth together with the slightly chewy skin. Yums...salivating while ‚Ä¶
One crab cost $50+ and did not taste good. The pepper crab that I ordered was of poor standard and disappointing! Waste of money!

(Translated by Google) After several times, I finally decided to give it a try today.
The conclusion is: an unexpected surprise. The food is delicious. The price is very reasonable. Will bring family and friends over.

(Repeated to go back with friends and family several times, everyone loved it. Attach photos here)

(Original)
