Great ambience and food, had the duck which is definitely their specialty, the lamb leg which did not taste like mutton at all  but if you're into that mutton taste maybe this isnt for you. Loved their eight treasures tea as well. The pork ribs were a little too sweet for my taste but if you like sweet bbt this is the dish for you. Also ordered the assorted vegetables and xiaolongbao and pan fried dumplings, which did not disappoint.

Was around the corner so came to try out this place based on the good reviews on Google. Like most reviewers mentioned, this restaurant really does give a homely vibe. Ordered a bento set (recommended by staff) and a katsu curry don. Bento set of  $15.80 is really value for money as there was 8 dishes in a bento box. Curry was really good but katsu was too tough. Almost 5 stars, but we waited 20-30mins for 2 packets of takeaway so minus 1 star.

Came here for my husband‚Äôs birthday and had a wonderful experience. The staff were super attentive and friendly, the food was such a treat, everything tasted so good.
We had the aburi otoro handroll, lamb rack (this was **chefs kiss** best of the night), spicy baby corn, tanoke classic bowl (strip loin), pork jowl, shisho lychee sorbet (super refreshing) and matcha pannacotta.

I'm nor sure abt recommended  tis  as had bad experience with the staff there who making the drink total Rude !!! As for  food bought Penang Kway Teow not sure  abt the specialty as looking at it jst normal  Kway Teow tho. Plus it's very pricey.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Located about 4minutes away from Tg Pagar  mrt. The fish is fresh and tasty. Yang chow fried rice can be improved with more eggs added. Fried beef was ok. Staffs are very friendly.
Old school,authentic kampong style Nasi Lemak and other dishes,selling at bygone era prices!! What are you waiting for?!

Ordered this Nasi Lemak for $4 and comes with chicken wing, egg, fish cake, Ilan bilis and peanuts.

The rice was really fluffy and had adequate coconut. Really goes well with the chilli with was slightly spicy and sweet. The other ingredients were okay.
Good food at affordable prices. Already crowded on a normal weekday. Ample parking in front of coffee shop.
The food was awesome.My fav was there chicken curry with parata *must try* . The staff over there really very kind and fast service.Wl recomend to other friend and visot soon.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: The standard has dropped drastically. The Ëë±Ê≤πÈ•º is literally like prata with a tiny count of spring onions. Where is the supposedly copious amount of Ëë±ÔºüNext, the fried rice was bland, not much of wok hei. Last feedback was that the ÊµÅÊ≤ôÂåÖ was steaming hot outside but cold on the inside. Granted that they got it changed eventually but the deed was already done. I love Crystal Jade but this time was very disappointed. Hope they improve.

If you like Indian cuisine, you can have a try here. We often have our breakfast with eggs prata here. This shop is very busy at peak hour, you have to queue at least 20 minutes to 30 minutes at peak hours

Such a pity. Food was good but overall experience was ruined by the staff in a white uniform, which I understand was the assistant manager. Very unwelcoming and hostile as a service staff. What was supposed to be a happy and positive experience was turned sour the moment we entered, no thanks to the Asst manager. Pls consider retraining this staff if he is going to be the first point of contact for all patrons.
Seriously good thai food here. Of all the thai kitchens in Toa Payoh, this is my favourite. Always satisfying to have a meal here.

Ive been to the bussorah outlet a few times. Decided to celebrate my birthday at winstedt this time. It was simply fabulous. Our server was new but she was so bubbly and friendly it was a joy to have her host us this evening.

Had the premium set dinner for 2 pax. The crispy papaya salad was nice, and crispy of course.
The steam fish was fresh, and a big slice of fish! Tom Yam Creamy soup was great too.
And choose 1 meat dish. We chose basil pork. Was nice, but I was too full to eat. Had it takeaway instead.

I ordered Thai milk tea but decided to add pearl. Staff gladly changed for me. Very good service. The drinks are served in takeaway containers and sealed with the machine to avoid spillage.

Overall nice restaurant, would come back again for sure!

Friendly place. I was pleasantly surprised by the variety of cooked food this humble place serves. The prata gravy is much better than the one at Springleaf and Casuarina. Much much better.

Parking is also ample and convenient. Worth repeated visits.

They have quite variety of food types such as Malay nasi padang (nasi campur), chicken rice, Ayam penyet, rojak, mee soto, etc.
Taste is OK, nothing to boast of.
They don't have much table, tend to be quite crowded during lunch hour.

Expect crowd during peak hours.
Super fast service.
Dine-in area available but to abide with the current regulations during this pandemic.
A lot of items are selling fast here especially during lunch time.
Packed during breakfast hours too.

best shengjianbaos I've had in Singapore! Even their xiaolongbaos are really good. also love their side dishes especially the Â§ßÂõõÂñú. only thing that I didnt enjoy is their ÈÖíÈÖøÂúÜÂ≠ê dessert. Salted egg sesame balls dessert were also really good but quite oily.

After dine-in was lifted to 5 pax, my friends and I wanted a cosy and family style eating place.  Location should be convenient with MRT station nearby.
We made our reservation at Gu Ma Jia Private Kitchen.  The lady who took our reservation was very friendly and thoughtful.
Our table was reserved at level 2, which was not noisy. It alowed my friends and I to catch up after not meeting one another for 35 years.
Food was great with generous portion.   Price was very reasonable.   Staff was friendly and attentive, even came to ask us how was food.
Overall, ambience, food and staff were great!

Nice restaurant in the middle of a park. I like the outdoor ambience - very casual and chill. Service can be improved because it took some time to take order. Food was pretty good! I like the skewers, toriyard sushi and fried squid. They have an extensive list of sake. Great sake menu and I love their cups. Overall will visit again! :)
Went on a Saturday afternoon, it's a nice cosy and well decorated restaurant. Ordered Ebi Fried Curry and Tonkatsu Curry. Both are okay curry. Service was good.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: It use to be good but now getting worse and worse‚Ä¶.

Air-conditioned and have a big variety of beer selections.  Food selection is good. Indian booth is popular choice, while most Chinese sample the flaming duck. Western booth is ok but takes forever to cook.

This place should have a 0 star rating. All staff who take order and cook have bad attitude in accepting your order.
Worse is the wanton noodles counter. Saw the lady rinsing her fingers into the pot for cooling the noodles twice. Very unhygienic.
This place does not accept cashless payment. Whatever cash that she handled went into the water for cooling the noodles.

Came here for dinner.

Bee hoon goreng ikan bilis was not bad. But could use more ikan bilis.
Mutton soup was good and flavourful. Mutton was tender as well.
Masala dosai had slight crispy edges. Also not bad.

They also have prata promotion available only on weekdays. 2 plain or 1 egg and 1 coffee or tea for $3.30 which we got but didn't photograph cause I was hungry. Prata was good and curry was great. Tea was good as well. Doesn't have the astringent taste.
Generous portion but waiting time is super long. Mee goreng is salty. Dosa is ok.
good value for money!  Wendy Tan is the best waitress  Ive ever encountered in Singapore. Very friendly and she seems enjoy her work fully.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content:
Rude female PRC staff horrendous service! Ordered pick up via foodpanda by self pickup, late by 25mins! No apologies!
During the 25mins waiting there, I have noticed the hygiene standard at the restaurant was very poor.
Food was salty, oil and full of msg.

First time trying this place on a weekday dinner. No queue. Was invited to join an extended family gathering dinner. Did not managed to take many pictures because was busy entertaining people. Parking is easy. The place is renovated like the environment for wedding dinner. Food and price are decent but I dont like the fish maw soup. Prompt customer service, friendly staff. Worth trying this place with family.

Great dining experience at Putien Northpoint. The food was delicious and the service team was amazing. It was a fantastic way to celebrate my grandmother's birthday, especially because the staff were really attentive and welcoming to her. Would highly reccommend this place to everyone!
Good enough for me.

Visited the restaurant on Wednesday Night, we needed to wait for about 10-15 minutes since all the table were full at that moment. Ordered their set menu, comes with 2 bowls of Jjajangmyeon and one bowl of Tangsukyuk (sweet and sour pork), ordered one small portion of Fried chicken with soy bean sauce, portions are generous. Comes with free flow of drinks, kimchi, radish, onion and the small dot of black sauce.
Nice dim sum buffet and reasonable price
Wonderful Thai food and very friendly staff and service! The oysters were fresh and yummy. We also ordered grilled pork, steamed sea bass and pork trotters. All were good.

A diamond in the rough.

The best no-frills cheeseburger I've ever eaten.

The grilled brioche bun is amazing, and the beef is seasoned well (for those who are not into savoury foods, this is slightly on the salty side).

You can ask to separate the shredded raw cabbage so that the burger would be only cheese + patty + bun.

The other items on their menu are great too, such as the pork belly which has an amazing charred taste and the beef brisket (can be a little fatty sometimes, but the sauce is great).
The food here is awesome.had their fish briyani n the portion is great with affordable price..worth..üëçüëçüëç

Loved their food so much and most of the food are much better than genki. Their sashimi is super fresh and reasonably priced. Waiting time is not too long too. Must must order their waffle ice cream because ITS AMAZING. I loved the chocolate one as it has choco bits inside. I think its some kind of japanese brand ice cream you can get elsewhere but anyway just eat it!!

You will also get token to their claw machine for every certain amount spent which i cant rmb off hand. But you can try your luck for a cup ice cream there. Hopefully they have more outlets (esp the east) and i'll be sure to visit üòã

I give this place a 1 star because the food is really depressing , the fish and chicken are so small that it does not fill your stomach.Missing side dishes  like the onion rings which was supposed to be 4 per person actually was only 2! And the fries , alot but missing 1 packet , also found a piece of fries that was fried with some strings in it  which was gross. With the price of the fish costing 7.90 and getting such a small portion of it , i will rather eat burger king or macdonalds which is more worth it. I reco not to buy in bulk as they may give missing side dishes.
Fresh ingredient at a reasonable and affordable price. Well marinated meat! Definitely will come back again.
Food is very yummy, and place is very bright and roomy. The croffle and chicken was a big hit with everyone, and I loved the chicken burger as well.
Food is okay, able to satisfy my supper hunger. Not crowded and and easy to find a parking lot.

Great chicken rice of course!
Service was great and staff were friendly, food was served relatively quick
Usually gets crowded during peak hours

My first impressions...
4* - Putien noodles.
4.5* - fried mixed veg with lotus roots
4.5* - fried towel gourd veg
3.5* - yellow croaker (too much Chinese wine added when served) if you like strong taste then it's good to go for it..
4.5* - Service is good

The place does a weekend high tea dim sum buffet which is pretty decent and good value. The buffet has a good range of dim sum and other Chinese dishes. Food quality wise, pretty good since this is after all part of Tung Lok. Service is efficient, and ordering is all automated. Prices seem reasonable.

The restaurant is fantastic because the food is always consistently good. The restaurant is better than many of their other locations because the tables are widely spaced apart from each other, giving you lots of room to move around and chat without disturbing neighbors. I There is a long queue during dinner hours so come early or later.
Worth the queue - tastes very similar to what you‚Äôll get in msia, according to my msian friend. Will be back again!
Always manage to get the place to sit. However the pricing has stayed flat but the quantity has reduced.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Very affordable indian food in a restaurant style setting. Depending on your indian food craving, do take note that they have different menu options for breakfast, before 5pm and after 5pm.

I went during lunch and really like their sets which comes with quite a few sides. The gobi manchurian is much tastier than the chickan manchurian (price point is the same fyi!). Their naan is on the thinner side so order more if you are going for that. Stuffed paratha came really piping hot and the teh tarik was good!
Not your usual tasting restaurant. Some dishes are possibly unique to them. Salt baked flower crab 4@52. Pretty good. 3.5ish to 4... Crab and pork with garlic are towards 4.

I ordered the salted egg crabs and fried mantou. Chef picked the good ones and as requested, was given good amount of sauce. It was really yummy and we enjoyed it a lot. Thank you! Êµ∑‰∏≠ÊûúÁÑ∂ÊúâÂÆù„ÄÇ

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Enjoyed the chicken rice and dishes. The chilli with ginger was fantastic. Roasted chicken meat was delicious. I usually judge the chicken rice by the soup and this was tasty too. I asked if I could top up the soup and they said yes!  I like my chicken rice with gizzard and liver and was happy to have these options. We added crabmeat omelette and prawn fritters which were yummy too. Recommended. Will be back if I need another filling of chicken rice.

Foods so so only but still ok
Service not so good also. Will recommend go and try but might not be go next time. End up didn't expect price $33+ per person
Well seasoned chicken, tasty black pepper sauce and always freshly fried fries. Very underrated store

Decent, homely! The zhajiang noodle is AMAZING. U should really try it if u are there. The fried rice is decent because of the after taste. When I first bite it, nothing special but I like the lingering after taste. The sweet and sour pork is a little too sweet for my liking. Too much sauce.

The fried dumpling, I love it! Overall ,not bad but the beer is really expensive
Waiter not very friendly.

We tried four soups, tomato, chicken teochew and kimchi. Tomato was rice and smooth, sweet n tangy, great for kids and adults. Teochew was obviously good. Chicken broth was nice and light. Kimchi soup was not too spicy. Beef were all good, ad well as signature dishes. Everything was fresh.

Service was good, staff very responsive and quick to clear empty plates. Prices quite high though, three adults and two kids the bill came to $250

Delicious butterfly pea dyed Nasi lemak. Set with chicken wing (choice of regular or turmeric) is a good buy.

The sambal is perfect, ikan bilis and peanuts very crunchy and yummy. Liked the food so much decided to pack it home for family. Will definitely be back!

Aunty peggy @ the yishun outlet is very friendly. Nice n cheap ramen fix. Clean store too.
Will visit again.

This is not a review of all the stalls in general, but one specific dessert stall here.   For $1.80, the portion is not only small, the bowl used is so shallow - totally not worth the price.  All water & not much barley nor bean curd skin.  If not for the ‚Äòok‚Äô taste, I would give it a one star.  Not worth another visit / patronage.

We ordered their signature chicken braised with cabbage and also tao fu with jin chng gu & spinach - very yummy. Their prices also reasonable. The waitress also very good - she advised us above 2 dishes enough to eat for 3 of us which is true. Fully recommend this place.

Lady boss is friendly and staff is helpful. Food had variety and its good for family gathering. With 5kiddos that quick picky eater is surprisingly a good place for mummy enjoy food and kids can do their own food eating and services.

Sisig is nice. Beer is ice cold and good price.

Just manage your expectation. See menu and actual order. üôÇ

Food is okay. Really like their mash potatoes but by the time evening comes, the mash potatoes is out of stock. So, if you want to eat mash potatoes, must come earlier. Service still okay la, lady boss sometimes polite and nice.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Wide range of variety of food and drinks, Prata is freshly make. Highly recommended
‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è super friendly stuff and amazing food! it‚Äôs a must try üòã

Both horfun and hokkien mee are not under their "all time favorite", true, both definitely are almost tasteless although with lots of gravvy. Both definitely not reco.

Small area thus seating is limited with some seats being squeezy

I'll give closer to 3.5 stars. The food is tasty (sorry we eat 1st take pic later), but portion is on the small side. Average $6 for 3 pieces of dim sum. Service is slow due to large amount of folks there. Table flow generally quite fast cause staff are quite prompt in clearing tables.
Go to their website to purphase a $99 voucher for free peking duck.
Molten salted egg lava bun is fantastic.
Fish maw is not tasty. Didn't soak up the broth.
Always good value for money. Family place.
Awesome Indian food. Great prata and curry (fish). Generally almost everything you order here is great-tasting especially from their Thai menu.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Food nice & cheap high recommend
Nice fish curry.
Terrible service

üòïüòüüôÅ Was there two night ago. Overall experience,  ambient not there , serving so so, pay first before you eat. The dishes that I have order , Only the San Lou Mee Hoon and garlic chicken taste Okay . The Sambal Sotong not fresh and super hard to chew. The rest not worth mentioned. For me the Bao Fa Tradition Food  claypot rice at Bukit Batok is so much tasty then here. ü•¥üôÑüòï
There is a bakuteh stall near the chendol stall.  soo garlicky good.   The chendol is perfect dessert match
Nvr disappointed

From pratas to biryanis, Srisun got you covered. You can get indian rojak, mutton soup, murtabak, mee goreng roti john and thosai to fulfil any craving of the hour at this 24hr joint. Don't forget to take on a hot cup of tea or a delectable serving of Milo Dinosaur with your meal.

Food is great and cosy restaurant setting. Attentive staff however they are pretty understaffed. Hopefully they will increase staff again now that it‚Äôs all opening up. We enjoyed the snowflake dumping and assorted mushroom dishes the most.

Dim sum was pretty good and portion alright, slightly on the pricier side. Quite like their Liu Sha Bao (fried egg custard buns)! A little bit expensive for $3 per pax for tea with peanuts though. Not the easiest of place to get a carpark lot, was charged close to $10 for parking at the other open car (hotel one perhaps) beside the public open carpark for less than 90 mins.

By far the worst mookata I've eaten in my life. no marinate for the meat and the soup is basically hot water. Really damn sad. Please, if you want to include mookata please at least have a minimal standard to upkeep.
Butter Chicken was amazing, the texture and flavour was so yummy ‚Ä¶ loving it .. thanks

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Nice solid value for money dim sum. Not the most refined but it's comfort food like what I've been used to. Nothing less. Will visit regularly.
So slow. Wasted my time for nothing special yet slow.

Probably one of the largest store in the island. Lots of varieties to. Goose from .. sashimi, sushi, grilled fish, Tempura and with high quality fish like blue fin tuna sashimi and Uni! Lovely place to have casual dining but the waiter and waitress needs to be more attentive. The oyster with cheese and special sauce taste funny with bitter after taste! The quality of the food is quite good and price is reasonable. Good for family too.!
Had the buffet which is very worth it. The taste the portion all excellent.

Ordered the beef brisket which to my opinion was way TOO dry, really not up to a restaurant standard. The set was around $13, portion was ok, just the quality of the meat has been extremely disappointing.

Hubby tried the duck leg confit which was better although also overcooked. He had the pasta as the side, seasoning was not bad but again pasta was over cooked.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Nice food and excellent service üòçüòçüòç I will come again

It's new !!! Have outdoor (pets allowed) and indoor seating. Nice, clean, spacious and cosy. Ordered the all day breakfast set which was tasty and a cafe latte. Will visit again. Only complain was the need to improve their online menu with picture of the food!

Good staff attitude! They are approachable, and even go for the extra mile! My last dish was Sheng Mee before snow fungus dessert. As I was already full, I asked for Sheng Mee to be packeted. The staff came back with 2 separate pack of the Sheng Mee and the gravy, this ensures the tastefulness even consuming it hours later.
The dishes are fresh and well cooked, with condiments nicely sparkled.
Worth considering coming back for another great meal
Love the place and the foods!

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: I would rate zero star if can...ordered via foodpanda and the package missed out one of the add-on order. Taste wise so so...portion small and not worth the $$ value.

Terrible attitude ladies at the counter. Like as if owe them money. They are like boss.
Won't recommend if ladies dun change.

I ordered fried kway teow with cockles through grab app. It‚Äôs very delicious. Cockles are very well cooked and no fishy. They added lots of red chilli for me as I requested. Will definitely order again. Thank you.

The food is really bad. Cereal prawn dish, the prawn not cooked. Served vegetables to wrong table and still wanted to serve the same dish to us. Rest of the food is below standard. The cleanliness of the coffeeshop is also really bad.  Won't be going again.
Ordered delivery for Mother's Day. Delivery was prompt and the food were yummy! The standouts were the Kong Bah Bao and Fried Prawn with Pumpkin Cream!
I love the mee goreng, It is not oily and yet tasty. A great place to enjoy coffee.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Firstly, took my order wrongly. Never mind I don‚Äôt mind change roasted duck to char siew. But look at the portion! This is pathetic! One star for the char siew which is quite decent. But roasted pork is dry and tastes horrible! There is a weird taste in it! And it was cold. One of the worst roasted pork!

Suggest to avoid Northpoint branch if you have more than 5 pax but sitting separately. They won‚Äôt accept even though the group is going to be split into less than 5 with the same household and sit apart.
Rendang is great, but I kind of hope they would give option for addition of juicy cucumbers into rendang set meal to balance out the dish.
Interesting grilled fish that is kind of fried.
Last photo is Teriyaki Beef Don. Definitely worth every penny

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: ok.. so when are they closing down?

Super expensive place to eat! Peri peri chicken main portion was so so small! Taste nothing to race about. Salmon main was okay. The chicken tikka pizza was good though. Ice lemon tea drinks were so diluted. No lemon taste at all.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Photo is misleading. I ordered on Foodpanda the thai basil pork with rice. The photo shows a fried egg but it came without. Taste is not bad though.

The best Malaysia Boleh In Singapore is in Jurong Point.  Upon entering, you can see how the rice dumplings is been wrapped as the rice dumplings festival is approaching.

The bak ku teh cum Claypot rice stand to have the longest queue.

Penang Chendol is 2 dollars and have standard here.
Nice place to find Malaysia food.

A regular recommended  ËÄÅÈº†Á≤âsaid very similar to Malaysia taste.

Semma serves up some of the best Indian food I've had! The satti sorrus are great and the mysore mutton is a must try. Great food. Great priced drinks.
11/10 recommend üôåüèæ
Foods are tasty but not so much to choose from as we came too early at 7:30am. Lontong servings size slightly smaller than others.

the service was bad ! asked for fish curry but gave dalca and took them a good 10 minutes (YED I TIMED IT) to change the gravy when the prata is already served . i overheard 1 of the waiter said to a lady customer "next time say extra sweet la" in a unhappy tone . patronise at your own will .
Tasty

Lunch promotion was lackluster... Food are quite good..

Price wise it's on the higher side..

Swatow Restaurant served lovely Tea Dim Sum at Toa Payoh. Food are great with Pleasantly Courtesy Service staffs namely Madam Tee, Madam Chua (Da Mei)
Both always smiley and very efficient with their service.
In fact most of service officers were very polite.

I had submitted a feedback that after I ate a bowl of this premium rice waygu bowl yesterday, I had diarrhea, suspected the foie gras not fresh etc.. No one call back to check at all.. Terrible.. Will not visit any of their restaurants anymore.

To myself, considering 7SGD for an order of pork chop or chicken cutlet is pretty high cost in heartland of AMK Ave 3, both meals taste and presentation do not possess the weight to fetch the amt. The pork chop is dry luckily the mushroom help that, the coleshaw is soggy and the tomato bean has blunt taste.

The only problem I had with the stall was I was way too unlucky. For a long time, I wanted to try this stall but the first 2 times I went(on different dates), I was greeted by a closed stall and a notice that says they will be closed for several days due to some reasons and that we had to check their FB as to when they will open again. So this time I checked... nothing means open and so....

This is my third visit to this stall and I finally got to try their extra power mee Soto and mee rebus for take away.  It was good that the gravy and soup were packed separately from the noodles so that even upon reaching home, the noodles weren‚Äôt soggy.  Both came with a large chicken thigh which is nice and tender.

Personally I find the portion too big for me, I should order the normal version next time without the chicken.  Otherwise taste is ok, nothing out of the ordinary.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Glad to get a table for 4 with no dinner reservation. Lo hei is good, generous portion even we ordered small. Service is great, staffs are very patient and paid special attention to serve peanuts and sesame separately for our friend with allergy.

Came here for dinner. The place is outside the main shopping mall. The staff were very welcoming and friendly. The gy≈çza was good. Ordered the tempura and it was great too. The tempura was done not to oily but just right. There are also some special ramen set that is value for money. The price was also reasonable.
Tastes good but quite expensive. This is 5.80, but 5 stars still cos yummy chilli.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
Great place to hang at the right time. Peak hours could get you to wait for 3 hours..
Good service, good food
I ordered 3 types of naan for takeaway. It should taste even better eating there. Will order again.

Looks like any other prata stall. They're located at AMK 603 Coffee Shop, which is at block 603 of Ang Mo Kio. Standard prata and mama stall offerings. They're apparently 24 hours, so in case any one has a supper craving, they'd be open, together with the drink stall. I wouldn't get anything beyond the roti prata in full transparency, and I'd definitely not come here specially for the food.
Ordered their truffle beef don, it‚Äôs really a MUST to try! Very delicious and affordable for the portion!!!

everything was fine, but just this male waiter in black shirt , simply just walk away ,after serving my food.
without listening to my new request order due to unable to order through the apps.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Best Ja jiang myeon I‚Äôve eaten! A little pricey but definitely worth the extra few dollars for authentic Korean food.
We had to wait 30min for a seat and when we entered, we were the only Chinese in the restaurant! Well patronized by Koreans.. had to be good!
Good old family style zi char

Opens till late so that is great for hungry peeps in hall. But not much variety (even tho the board shows so much food, not many available). When i was there around 9, there were only some veggie dishes and and meat and prata. The rest were not available.
Ordered the Premium Butadon and it was flavourful, the ratio of fat to meat is great and it literally melts in the mouth. I would definitely come back to try the other butadon and ramen.

Ordered the chicken chop with mushroom sauce ($7.90) for takeaway. One of the better ones out there, the sauce was thick and flavouful. The chicken chop was tender and juicy. Curly fries was nicely done too, crispy and fragrant. The corn was sweet and nice. Salad was average only. Will definitely return to try the other items.
Come and try.. üëç

Dine in the restaurant a little later after typical lunch time to avoid the crowd.

The admission was quick and friendly, the waitress came promptly to take our order and the meal was served up pretty quickly.

The food quality is good and the portion is appropriate for the price. However, the lack of the 5th star was attributed by the lack of attention from the staff, we have to wave our hands fanatically and called out loudly before I can get my chili sauce.

But the dining experience was saved by a senior (age, not ranking) staff who took over the service from the other one who was supposed to be waiting at our table. She was friendly and chatty but not overwhelming for us to enjoy our meal.

Interesting selection of drinks: dark chocolate milk, butterfly pea tea with lemon, rose tea, your classic coffees, etc. Recently opened! Happy to have a bit more variety in this food market. Owner is very friendly!
very good salmon. seems everyone in Q ordered this.  Ebi was nice. hwr Q needs 20-30min during lunch hr.

Rather disappointing experience that did not live up to the reviews and Google rating. Ordered four dishes:
-  Mongolian pork ribs : too dry
-beancurd with prawns : decent but nothing to rave about
-Heng Hua been Hoon: rather dry as well and not as nice as Pu Tien standard
-oyster omelette: fluffy and spongy but flavour is lacking.

Overall decent meal at affordable price but certainly not anything special.

Very dishonest practice and misrepresentation. The waitress gave us two plates of fish skin and said please try as appetizer, if you like it,you can buy two packets at 13.80. we asked if it's chargeable and she repeated the same to ask us to try.

One of my folks started eating the first plate and another waitress came and said it's chargeable.. we were shock and she said it's okay, she will bring one back and only charge one plate. It's covid season, they left food down when our masks were down and they took it back to serve another table ..

At the cashier I asked if they knew they were dishonest and many had complained, the cashier just smiled and kept quiet. She did not refund when I requested and just said," I will feedback".

Simply dishonest Canton Paradise staffs..
Patrons, please beware.
Good food but expensive

Old school taste, old school straight talking, bit actually friendly, auntie. We are taking deep fries chicken, cutlets, grilled meat, canned beans, fried buns and fries. Classic Straits style 'western' food food the 70s. It looks like the stall has been around that long too.

Maybe ask them not to fry the bun though. Unless you can lower your cholesterol at will.
Excellent place to unwind with some grade A5 wagyu beef and sake
food n service are pretty decent just like any of their similar outlets. due to it is in a heartland mall best to make advance booking.
portion versy small. salmon was maybe 3mm thin.. will not buy again..
Tasty food and good service
Prata was good and so was its curry. The only problem is the pricing. Had it been a little cheaper, it would have been better
Nice environment to dine in, cheap and good. Compare to other Indian restaurant, this one is cheapest. Friendly staff, can go and try thier set menu, super worth it.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Soild and good food but abit pricey depending what you choose. Beef and fish surely $7 plus and above and quene is long during office and no parking place.
We had 25% off during lunch. Order before 12:30pm on weekday. Service crew was efficient and good in recommending. üëçüèªafter discount our bill was about $100.
The dim sum dishes were not bad.

Great neighbourhood cafe with brunch food. Rather big space lots of seating outside and inside. We ordered the fried chicken and croffles, mentaiko fries and the mushroom risotto.

The fried chicken was really well battered, light and crispy and not oily. The coleslaw was also a really nice touch cause I‚Äôm not a fan of putting maple syrup on my savoury food. I would say a must try when you come here.

The mushroom risotto was everything you would want in a risotto dish. Simple and rice was cooked just right (slightly Al dente but cooked through).

Mentaiko fries were decent but nothing special.

You order and pay through a QR code which is always a plus.

The yellow chicken curry, the black ink squid n Soto beehoon  are my favorite dishes here. Like their veggies too. The place is usually clean n its not too crowded even though they are popular for lunch.  Also like that their Kopi, bandung n lime juice is cheap n good. Their food is better than the Malay stalls at Amk hub food court or  the stall at Amk Mrt. Average price per plate $5.50
Ambience good. Quite quiet. Warning for sinfully oily flavorful food.

ordered from grab. ask for fried chicken but got curry chicken. there‚Äôs a reason we choose fried because we want to eat THAT. next time if dont have , dont display and contact us.i thought i can escape the bad reviews but looks like i have to join in. pls improve or change staff thanks. and no i dont want to contact.
ownself check ownself
Food is OK and price reasonable

Ok to satisfy your Malaysian hawker food cravings without going over the causeway you could count on fei xiong group.  This is one of their branches that's compact enough to squeeze in multiple stores. Price point is very reasonable in Singapore context. Food quality is passable. One of those no frill tummy fill eatery. Coffee and tea is surprisingly cheap. If you are in City Square and want some hawker style food. You may give this place a try .

Find it a really average place. Fish maw soup comes w lil ingredient n soup not thick enough. The fried pork n the pine apple rice so so only too

Only thing it‚Äôs not expensive but I won‚Äôt come back since food so so
Best Nasi Lemak In SG

Really good butadon, though we prefer the original one as compared to the premium iberico version which is more expensive, to each their own. The only downside was that it wasn‚Äôt filling since the portion was relatively small.

The ramen on the other hand, was really poor. The taste and portion were not up to mark at all.

That said, this is a plus for solely the butadon which is what they are famous for.
Happy hours discount is fabulous. Comfort food to the max

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: A cosy embience for family or friends get together.  Great customer service and yummy food varieties. Went for lunch on Saturday with mixed feelings about late waiting time and customer service however I  was truly surprised that all the  7 dishes we ordered arrived with less than 15 minutes wait.  Kudos to Mr Maari for recommending the chef's weekend specialities too. Will surely go for dinner soon.

Had a wonderful dinner . Gud recommendation by the cashier girl and great service by the guy named Danes who served us. Food was soo good and delicious . The restaurant was soo clean and comfort to eat . Will b back again

Me and my partner had their truffle pork chop and that alone made us give this simple down to earth restaurant five stars. The meat was juicy, savoury, succulent and satisfying. Everything was on point. The onion rings were crunchy and perfect. Mac and cheese was delicious too. The only underwhelming thing was the strawberry smoothie, compared to the meal.
If you like your food served AN HOUR after your ordering. This is your first choice.
Veg & non veg Indian foods with high price. Valuable foods for high price

Have a great time with friends here... Tempura not bad, could be better. Enjoy the desserts, delightful ending after a heavy meal, must try the special dessert! Server are friendly but might be a little bit understaffs as we needed to wave a few times before they can attend to us.

My fav dim sum joint !
Love their egg tarts , siew Mai , har kao, chicken claws and more !!
The one who serve with bad attitude if u only buy 1 set

Celebrate family birthday here. Use GE voucher for Safra Jurong West branch. Average customer service as no smiles but service is prompt and businesslike. Food presentation can be improved as it can be better than Collins.

Who doesnt love BBQ?

Yakiniku offers BBQ lovers a quick and easy way to enjoy it, without the long preparation times and smells on your clothing.

Prices are affordable and value for money.

Quite a popular chain restaurant, so do come early.

This outlet is self service, very intuitive for customers that listen to instructions from the staff or who bother to read the signs. No fuss dining.

wenr arnd lunch time.. wait arnd 5-10 for our orders to be taken as they are busy. Prata is very delicious. Came w curry and daal. theres a small mutton fats w it. curry is spicy üëå. The teh ais is sweet to my liking. Just the food is on the slightly expensive side. Overall a pleasant experience

Well firstly, this is Halal Ramen broth for those who came here thinking it's pork  tonkotsu broth. So great to eat with Muslim friends!

Portion and price point wise is pretty okay. Its the flavours that feels abit off. The miso Ramen was really thick and salty. Abit hard to drink the soup it's more like a gravy. I rate: 2/5 üåü

Veggie Ramen had a huge portion of noodles and veggie so pretty full and light flavours. I rate: 3/5 üåü

Condiments really helped to give more flavours in the Ramen as per ur liking.

A nice cafe tucked away from the hustle and bustle of the city. Consists of both indoor air conditioned and outdoor seating suitable for pet owners which is a plus. Ample seating space inside as the restaurant stretches quite far in. Service is good and relatively fast. Decor is pretty and they have interesting pieces of furniture and contrasting wallpapers and panels for a varied effect. Tried their speculoos latte and Peter‚Äôs Pancake which is quite good üëçüòä

really a good place to chill ... feels like being in Japan
the food is excellent and fresh
MUST TRY

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Such a terrible services, waited for almost 2 hours and then they said the food I ordered don‚Äôt have and cancel my order without my concern. Don‚Äôt even wish to give one star

Mee rebus with chicken is delicious! The chicken is not shredded chicken, but bigger pieces. 1 whole hard boiled egg. What makes it special is the satay sauce drizzled on top. Taste wise,  this mee rebus is sweet. The soto ayam is good too.

Standard is still good after 1 year. But price has increased. Mee rebus with chicken is now $4.50.
Ordered fish and chips at 5.50. The aunty told me to wait 7min to collect as there are a few orders in front of me. The fish and chips is normal standard. Probably could have provide more fries.
Fast service, a bit long Q after 9.30 am, Prata good n the butter chicken so yummy

One of the best set lunches I had in Jack Place. Many outlets quality of food was not good and felt presurized to clear the table fast but this outlet in Toa Payoh has excellent service, food quality and ambience.

Asked for extra pork lard for my wanton noodle, the stall assistant proceed to give me a 10min lecture of how expensive pork lard is and I have to pay extra $0.50, which is a very small amount as $0.50 cannot even buy bread nowadays.

Attached photo of a Ba Chor Mee I bought elsewhere with extra pork lard, no extra charges required.

Seems like Malaysia boleh not boleh already

Wide selection of sake, nice food and staff is friendly..the BBQ selection for those who is keen... order Edamane- boiled
soy bean, truffle chawanmushi (nicely present and rich serving of ingredients hidden in the egg with a little garnish of truffle)
Temputa moriawase (prawn)
Aspara asparagus with pork belly
Hotate- scallop with bacon
Buta bara- gfilled pork belly
Kawa-chicken skin
Tsukune- homemade chicken meatball
And not forgetting the Supume ika grilled japanese squid, (totally love it)
And a sake to go with it.. yummy....

Pasta is quite good, but the prawn is stuck to its shell & hard to deshell.

The brownie ice cream dessert - the brownie is too sweet; it needs the ice cream to dilute the sweetness.

Unfortunately Buddy Hoagies had removed waffles from its menu, which was one of the highlights for visiting. It‚Äôs disappointing and we might not be going out of our way to visit it as a result.

Super Value for money. You can have food at peace. You can‚Äôt go wrong with your choices here. I love Teh Halia here especially along with tomato onion uttapam. Pls note tomato onion uttapam is not on the menu. You can request them to make one for you. It‚Äôs yummy. Curry along with egg parantha has just the right flavor to excite your taste buds. Don‚Äôt expect too high about ambience. If you Wana taste genuine taste, then this is the place to go for.

Overall good experience.
The grill food is well cooked not charred.
It's tender as well.
Minus one star is because charashi Don is not available today üòî hence ordered sashimi to satisfied my cravings. Overall yummy üòã

Food is cheap! Total damage $45.50 for 4 mains and some skewers.
Highly recommend suan cai yu, tomato egg and skewers. 5/5
The broth in suan cai yu was really flavourful and addictive. Great to have on a rainy day.

As for the spinach dish, the vegetables is towards the dry side. But taste wise is okay. Would give it a rating of 3/5.

For the dumpling, was pretty disappointing. Soup was bland & dumpling was tasteless. Rating 1/5.

Overall, for the price point, food is worth it! Would definitely visit again to try their grilled fish & mala!
Love it here, the dim sum still up to standard, just hate the long queue

A friend of mine came to Shami Banana for help to use restroom  coz she's not well holding her tummy, looking pale & the lady in the restaurant told her restroom is being clean but my friend saw 2 customers coming out & there's no cleaning done .Such a heartless lady to use such excuse to reject my friend because she's not dinning in .Very disappointing with the staffs too especially those who are serving dishes because I had been there, too
Ordered food with payment & waited for one hour they said no more food.A lousy restaurant.
Will be 5 star rating if aunty taking order wasnt rude. Not once but twice!!!

The food was tasty and the ambiance was privatize . We had our dinner here and its like a 'omakase' style . Where the chef prepare whatever that suits your taste . Please advice your preference of dietary and style .Booking only... No walk in ....

The price of food is quite reasonable. The taste was OK for some of the food. The shop also offers quite a number of "China" style food (which we happen to not order).

The services is also good as they will help to top up hot water for drinks as well as help to pour the tea.

Definitely will comeback
Surprise the variety not that many...lok lok served is too dried after fried...
Personally feel the food slightly above average but not like fantastic, price on the high side !
Had been coming here for quite a few times. Service here here is good . food taste great and the staff is friendly.
Old school kind of western food. The price is reasonable and tasty of course! Had their chicken cutlet, fish and chips, chicken chop and chicken wings.

One of the renowned and authentic prata houses. Prices of food served are slightly on the high side but  make up with the quality of food. The restaurant, though, needs to improve in terms of its furniture and overall cleanliness.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Came here with my family, was here many years ago but decided to bring my family to try the Teochew cuisine. We ordered those dish with great reviews and recommended by other reviewers. I must they they don‚Äôt disappoint, all the food we ordered were really good. Specially the braised duck, slices so thin it almost melts in the mouth. Don‚Äôt be deceive by the Ngoh Hiang, it looks normal, but just wait till you bite into it, makes you wanted more. The fish is really fresh and cook just nice. The vegetables is ok as I am not a fan. The Oyster omelette is really worth the wait, I was wondering why it took so long, it need skills to cook a simple dish to taste so good. Finally my all time favorite, Orh Nee, I have love it since young and none is better than this. Will come back for more in the near future. Highly recommended.

First time at coffee shop in Block 631 AMK Ave 4. Tried mee soto at Mahan. The taste was great, spicy and sweet, yummy combo. Lots of chicken given, all for only $3.50. Malay food lovers should give this stall a visit

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Quite disappointing on the food. Service is not at even a basic expectation especially from the manager. When order food, did not explain the time left for food when ordering. Only have less than 1 hour to finish the food. Ask the manager ‚Ä¶

Ambience wise nothing to shout about .
Order the fried tengiri , do eat when freshly fried else the fishy odor comes out .

Xing hua fried bee Hoon and stewed toufu was nice .

Today I ordered Tandoori Chicken from this restaurant. I got it packed and when I opened the box there were just 2 small pieces of tandoori chicken. Sad part is this is not at all worth for its price ( 7.60SGD).   This is very expensive and tasteless. If you wana try tandoori chicken please skip this place.
My favorite Indian Rojak stall at Yishun.
Making reservation but was told that they are closed for renovation till Dec22. Its best to call before go down to avoid disappointment.
There are some unique dishes that worth a try at the famous kitchen. However quite disappointed with one  "unfresh" flower crab that was mixed in our order!
Nice, friendly and pretty Chef. Their western is so good. Among the best in the area. The portions are big. Fries and salad are old school. üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª
Definitely an underrated place. The food is super good and pricing is fair. The spicy salmon udon is a must try!

All the stalls are now open though some delicacies like the popiah was nowhere to be found during this pandemic.. this eating spot in Jurong Point have food stalls featuring the famous dishes from the popular locations in Malaysia like Penang and Ipoh.
The signature rice noodles was freaking weird to me. Pork rib, prawn, Shao Rou, stewed chicken, fish... A failed exploration
Reservations made online on Quandoo are not entitled to existing promos or discounts.. No reservations needed anyway, they are very empty.

Kind of reluctant to recommend this great little Japanese eatery as it will surely be more crowded than it already is. Friend had the truffle beef and it was juicy and flavourful. I had the spicy salmon bowl which reminsces of spicy salmon gunkan - fresh salmon with a chilli padi kick that is so satisfying. Service was friendly and prompt and the ambience was simple but cosy. Heartwarming and wholesome comfort food!
Good value for money with good portion of food. Taste great. Looks like a family run restaurant with friendly staff.

Disappointing. Added egg and they fried it with the rice so u cant eat it on its own. The photo is misleading as it shows a sunny side up. And ive eaten from other outlets and they always fry the egg separately.

Nice little Shanghai place, the food is nice. Try the spring veg roll, it‚Äôs not like what we eat outside.

The drunken chicken is also nice. And the fried pau is good too. Portion is rather small.

It‚Äôs popular, please remember to call and reserve a seat to avoid waiting
I had Oder food from deliveroo. And the noodles got something I have no idea what this but look like dead ant. And the Red Ruby look ugly I disappointed.
very friendly staff, and yummy food!
chun rong was very cheerful and helpful, service was very good
Signature Cai Pu Hor Fun and Signature Cai Pu Beancurd very shiok!!! üòãüòãüòã

Nice Yun nan noodle place in Singapore. So unique and tasty.

I had the sour and spicy soup, which was good and compatible with most of the ingredients. The soup taste was just alright, not too spicy, not salty.

Just a little feedback:

The noodle was too slight, probably it was soaked in the soup for some time before serving to me.

The fish slices and some ingredients were with bones. Suggested to substitute with boneless meat.

Other than that, all were perfect. Interesting interior design and attentive service too. Portion looked big but just alright for me.
Fried radish are in huge chunks, which is Malaysian-style, and they are fried with lots of eggs and taugeh! Super tasty and it‚Äôs only $3! Will definitely come again!
Pratas are fresh and the curries are delicious. The environment is mostly clean and very comfortable.

I see a lot of mixed reviews here so I decided to try for myself. Heard was quite hyped people queued for hours when it opened.
I visited on a weekday lunch there was no queue got immediate seating. Was quite cute there was a robot which showed me to the table. Way or ordering food was quite standard. Didn't like the table for 2 was really small and narrow.
Wowed by the menu. Didn't expect they had such a wide range of dishes, and the price was really cheap. Kept scrolling and took quite a while to order the dishes. Time taken for food to arrive was quite fast except for the Agedashi tofu, okay since they had to fry it upon order and it was hot when it arrived.
Was a hit for me for the food quality as I found them pretty good and satisfied. Nothing was not fresh or tasted bad and seriously nothing to complain for the price you are paying.
Things I didn't like was that the table for 2 was really small, so if you really order quite a lot of things you find yourself not having space to put the plates. They tried to consolidate orders by putting a few types of sushi in a plate but still the space was lacking.
Don't know if it's because of this the staff keep coming to the table trying to clear the plates. It was a mixed reaction because on one hand I found it quite disturbing wondering if the kitchen is lacking plates or they are trying to be nice to free up table space. I didn't like it when you are having a meal and conversation and the staff keep coming to disrupt.
Although the staff keep coming to clear the plates, when you need attention from them you just can't get their attention. They served the matcha cheesecake without any spoons we raised our hands for a few minutes before someone noticed us. Think it should be default to provide dessert teaspoons with the dessert or have some in the drawer under the table.
The only thing I felt funny was a female staff whenever she came to clear the plates she would always knock into something and go "oh my god oh my god".
Meal wise the bill was really reasonable. Enjoyed it.

The food is good but the service from a supervisor sux real bad. Very rude and loud. Take note most seats do not have back rest, chair not suitable for elderly. We changed the seats to those with back rear as we have 4 elderly diner and was scolded by the young supervisor and an elderly China waitress. Suggest to avoid Yishun Dian Xiao Er and go another branch instead or try Putien further down the corner which is a grade higher.
Not suitable to hold business meal here due to the low service standard.
Tasty Seafood Pad Thai served by friendly staff. A more wet version compared to other places.
Best $16 Ribeye steak, good qyality value
Service sucks given by a guy I say more than 3 times combo A keep asking if ur staff having a bad day don't vent it to the customer showing one type of face

Update for the month of December 2021
Nice renovated interior !
Bright and cozy.
Added some new photo.

Updated July 2021
Added New photo  :)
No changes ....Still 5 stars  :)

Update Review for the Month of May 2021 ( Just before No dining in :-) )
Added Some New Photo  ;-)
First of all, thanks to the chinese lady by the name of Yique for your excellent customer service. The Food came fast. ALL are very delicious and that includes the beverage that i have ordered ( Water Chest Nut + Ice Lemon Tea ) The Sweet And Sour Pork is NOT hard ....Surprisingly it was Tender and Juicy.... Oh and the French bean it was very very delicious....Loved it when mixed with the Minced Pork.... By the way i have lost count of how many times i have dine/pack away order @ this outlet  :-)

2020 Review This Canton Paradise @ Sengkang their Porridge is super delicious and their Roast Duck is SUPER Good.
Food was good and tasty. Service was prompt.

One of our family‚Äôs favourite seafood restaurant in Singapore. We cannot go there and not order the salted fish fried rice and kang king sambal...Food is very good and affordable, service is mediocre but kind of expected for how busy this place tends to be. Prefer lunch crowd, a little quicker service. But food is always great.
I ordered a Little San salad from this outlet at 8.45pm. Ingredients are still very fresh and overall taste is very good.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Absolutely a MUST AVOID place if you desire some form of service. The wait time for take away was over 40 minutes with no pre warning when the order was taken. Order sequence preparation based on who comes first doesn‚Äôt exist when people who arrived and ordered after us received their food before us. The staff were either simply just standing around OR moved like snails to fulfill and pack food that were already prepared and left on the tables. What an experience compared to the many Hong Kong street restaurants I have patronized elsewhere. In addition, the staffs‚Äô attitude were beyond rude. Go at your own RISK!
Poor customer service , the Chinese lady staff was very rude.

Despite being new, the place is full! Their menu seems similar to the one in riverwalk but the prices are cheaper if I recalled correctly. Food is good and tasty. Enjoyed the tempura items (soft shell crab and prawns) the most. Service is good too. We ordered too much for 2 pax.

Full house on a sat night due to restricted seating arrangement. Waiting time to be expected as they were attending to food delivery orders. Prata and gravy pretty good! Maggie goreng is spicy but very little portion of meat.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: One of the better Nasi Lemak is Yishun. The chicken wing is big, crispy on the outside and the inside meat is juicy but I feel that it is not marinate long enough. The mackerel otah taste good. The egg is a bit overcooked as I prefer egg with a bit of runny yolk. The portion of the sambal chill is generous. The only thing which I don't prefer is the rice, something seems just not right whenever I eat the rice as I feel it don't have have the very distinct coconut milk flavour and aroma of pandan leaves which a good nasi lemak should have.
Spacious restaurant with a modern deco. Attentive and prompt service. Good food.with little pleasant surprises.
Just ok for me. Honestly I felt quite pricey ($90+)for just 3 persons.

Got a queue number an hour and a half before.
Message notification was in accurate (it‚Äôs still okay acceptable maybe malfunction)

Upon returning to check for our queue status had already exited 2 queue number. Confronted the genki  staff Shirley. she lied in an uncouth manner saying that queue not in sequence.

However checking with another Chinese staff she claim that queue number should be in sequence since day 1 working in this outlet.

This is nonsense customer service provided by Shirley. Utterly speechless by such uncouth manner.

Hopefully genki would take this feedback into consideration. To improve on customer service relation instead of lying with eye wide open to your customer

Thank you
I visit frequently to order the lime steamed fish

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Visited the place for two times, and still amazed by how well-executed the noodles were!!! The noodles got a nice chew and very tasty! Most of the customers visited during lunch hour were Korean! I recommend Jjamppong the most!
Nice and cosy. Limited choices for food.
After living in India a couple of years it is great to finally find such authentic and wonderful Indian food near Yishun. We'll be back for sure.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: This place serves very good food. Affordable, good  authentic Thai food.
Very nice tasty dishes. Eveyone of us likes this place. Dessert was so-so on the other hand. Still, it's a good restuarant to patronise.
Quality prata, loved their egg prata. Other items are nice as well. Family friendly seating environment at Safra Jurong.

Nice place for a quick snack but also pairs great with the Ramen shop opposite it! They have an agreement where they lease part of the shop's seating to the Ramen store so you can enjoy the best of both worlds! The sweet teriyaki sauce complements the salty Ramen very well.
You can try the prata because it's really good but not the western food. Very expensive (range between $8-$15)

Just received my foodpanda order, paid $67 extremely not worth the price tag.
10+ sashimi which is super tiny portion
$9+ salad which is only lettuce with single tiny slice of avocado
$12+ of lousy made Ebi sushi
üòì total ripped off!ü§¶üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Lousy service, waited so long for food but still wrong order. Ask her to refund the difference since the order we recieved is cheaper, but she still got the cheek to talk back. Both drinks and food wrong. HORRIBLE. If i could give 0 stars, i would do that.
All the staff in The restaurant are very friendly and helpful. The food are good and they have very good promotion during 2.pm to 4.30pm Daily. 40%off on all food.
Not very long queue on a Sunday 1pm. I personally like the roasted pork. Crispy skin and savory. Just the noodles abit towards the soft side so i gave it a 4 star. Fast service. Affordable.
The waiter forgot to serve me my chicken n time but he came smiling sending me the dish, with apology. So, I didn't mind. Kindness matters.

Great service. maintain the good work.
Highly Recommended..

Ordered on Deliveroo and the food is great! Amazing quality for a coffeeshop Japanese joint. Will have to try them out on-site!

‚Äî‚Äî Added new pics from meals on-site!

A decent Japanese outlet to go to in the neighbourhood. Not the cheapest u can get but definitely one of the better choices.
Beef salad is always my best bet and salmon mentaiko is equally great!

Was having training at the nearby hdb hub. Visited this place for lunch. Ordered the simple wanton mee noodles. The char shu was good, but the wantons and the noodles were normal.  They included pork lard in the noodles and that‚Äôs why it‚Äôs pretty flavorful. Paid $5 for the wanton mee which I thought was slightly on the high side.
Fast service despite a busy Friday evening. Staff very friendly, good place for a no frills dinner.

(Translated by Google) Probably the junkiest KFC I've ever been to. Tell the clerk to pack, pay the 0.2 yuan plastic bag and then tell me that the beverage ca n‚Äôt be put in and I want to hold it in my hand or it will turn over. So what is the significance of my packing? The ordering machine is also broken. The production speed is also very slow, and even on weekends, there are many people waiting for meals. I have never seen KFC with such a poor service

This popular chain restaurant never fails to impress with its Samsui Ginger Chicken. In fact, every table had the dish on it. Spread the chopped ginger on the succulent and tender chicken pieces, wrap them with lettuce leaves and we have ourselves a bite of its signature dish. The order taker was very helpful in recommending a few dishes once we told her of our dietary requirements. The Claypot Salmon could do with a little less salt, but that is just my opinion. Service was efficient with our chrysanthemum tea constantly being refilled.

I grew up eating the Penang versions of prawn noodle soup and lor mee at this stall. The broth is extremely rich with the use of tons of prawn heads and shells I believe. If you want to try something different, order the dry prawn noodles with small prawns. The tiny prawns have been deshelled and cooked down to a shrivel but they are really delicious. If you upsize your order, you also get to enjoy some slices of lor bak and lor ng(egg) along with the prawns.
As for the lor mee, I always prefer bee hoon and upsized so that I get to enjoy more of the really well braised lor bak and a whole egg. Just typing this is making me drool againüòÅ

Do yourselves a favour and avoid the steak!

Great ambience, professional and friendly service crew, overall a fantastic respite within NTU. However, the food items were hit-or-miss. The salmon was fantastic, but the steak was... let‚Äôs just say, even a hawker stall could deliver better. Fries were tasty...pork fajita was alright, nothing really remarkable...

I‚Äôd give it a positive review only because on both occasions I patronised, I hadn‚Äôt paid the full price: first time was with an eatigo 50% discount, the next was for their $14 set lunch. Without these discounts, I‚Äôd feel disappointingly shortchanged, given the quality of the food - certainly does not command the √† la carte prices, in my opinion.

It has the potential to become a five-star establishment, as long as the consistency of the food quality improves. Everything else (service, ambience) is already in place for an excellent dining experience.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Food was great and portion are quite big. Worth the money
The food was fabulous. Also, the staff are honest and helpful. My friend dropped his credit card. They are guided us to conceign to collect the lost card. Thank you Emily and Li Zhen!

Avoid at all costs.

Service: absolutely terrible, especially the lady boss (tall). Gave attitude and black faced to first timers who was unfamiliar with the ordering system. Charge 10% service charge for lousy service.
Food: mediocre. Penang hokkien mee was soggy. Lok lok variety limited and unfresh. Ala carte 0.80 for one single beef ball.
Soup base: More like salted flavored water. Mala soup base was diluted++.

The only saving grace is probably the airconditioned environment.

Seriously, there are better lok lok places to dine at.
Prompt service, decent portions, but server attitude isn't the best here. 3 stars for taste of soy sauce chicken and charsiew, nicely charred and tender chicken
Nice ambience and food especially good service and friendly from Lynn..
Very nice pineapple rice and vege dish

(Translated by Google) Curry corner must eat

(Original)

You win liao!

The char Kuey Teow -passed
Ambla  drinks- passed
Laksa -passed
Nutmeg drinks - passed
Water spinach with squid - what happen to the sauce?
Fried pork belly with Red yeast rice fermented beancurd - Fantastic (must try)
The fried fish with Thai sauce and another one with sweet and sour sauce - passed
Pandan leaf chicken - juicy
Chendol - passed

Will come again

Recommended with 2 thumbs up

The ramen at Takagi are very affordable for the average Singaporean. Craving for some spiciness, we ordered the Karaka and their seasonal Chilli Crab Ramen.

Initially I thought how spicy can Japanese Ramen get, right? Then I realise I was wrong. The spicy ramen here at Takagi are really spicy. I enjoyed both the flavourful ramen especially that Ajitama Egg that is done well with runny egg yolk.

We also ordered the Nori Tempura with Truffle Mayo and their most popular Deep Fried Gyoza. Love the crispiness in both the side dish that added a crunch to our meals.
I tried the mala xiangguo mid spicy, no gravy, ingredients not fresh which i told them remove from display. Total $17 with rice and drinks for 1 person, not as what i expect from review.
The Signature Royal is sold out so I opt for Fried Chicken and Fish. Chicken is tender and juicy , rice is fragrance and chilli is the main draw.

Ordered a 7 course takeaway, peking duck and fish were good.
Drunken prawn soup no herbal taste, a lot of MSG taste
The red bean soup that came with it is very starchy

One of the really good Japanese restaurant chain, their pork rice bowls are nice, even better are the sashimi and salmon bowl with mentaiko sauce. Unfortunately their wagyu bowl are not really done well as the beef are a little chewy. Good place to chill with friends over some cold beer and nice Japanese food üëç
The best appam I ever tasted in Singapore even thou is $1 a piece but u really can taste the coconut...

I had the Dum Briyani Mutton ordered via grabfood along with some prata. The flavour of the Briyani is simply suberb. I love the rice, the spice, the curry, and the melt in your mouth juicy meat.

Also I had enough left over to eat a small meal the next day so it was money very well spent.

Bad experience ordering from foodpanda with this restaurant. Suppose to arrive at 1115 but waited until 12 am with no update from restaurants itself or foodpanda Last and never gonna order from them again

hello Ichikokudo, I ordered the Ichi beef ramen as shown in the picture. It looks nowhere like the clear broth in the picture. The marinated egg was also missing, had to ask for it. Is this a case of false advertising or misrepresentation?

Food is good, just not what I ordered.
Very nice and tasty don't think can find it else where

The queue starts at about 6pm for dinner. Overall, the food is pretty yummy. The buffalo drumstick is really flavourful and tasty. The sweet potato fries is crispy and soft, even though the sweet potato itself is not sweet. The black pepper medium steak is tender. The side salad comes mixed in a sour and sweet sauce which makes the vege very appetising. The prawn marinara spaghetti is al dente, and the prawn is very crunchy and lightly marinated with a salty fresh taste. The chicken chop taste great, and not so much fats. The oven baked haddock fish with penne is quite okay. The texture of the penne is just right, and the tomato sauce is nice and not too sour. The fish could have a bit more taste though. The add on mushroom soup is the standard kind, and can do better.

I sum up this place as a watering hole for ppl who miss KL food. Definitely can't beat the famous, authentic but hard to find KL Pasar Pudu wet market curry chee cheong fun. Ingredient-wise, Anson Town is a little more like Ipoh style with pig skin, long beans and thicker curry sauce (KL one has fu-zok, fragrant haebee & lots of sesame seed). I quite like their baked kaya kok (triangulated puff pastry with kaya filling) - not cheap but this is S'pore what. A must try for first-timers
Worst service and food is not good ! Very disappointed.

The Tonkotsu Special was tasty and reasonably priced. The noodles were cooked al dente and had a nice bite soaking up the Tonkotsu broth nicely. The chashu was slightly thicker and tougher than I prefer, but still good. The Tonkotsu broth was rich and smooth yet not overly salty. The torched chicken drumstick had a nice sear. The meat was juicy and tender, coming off the bone easily. I got it as an add on, so I would recommend getting it as part of the clear chicken broth for the full experience. The pork gyoza were a tad pricey, but the filling was very fresh and not mushy, while the skin had a light crisp. It was fried on order and nicely done. Overall a satisfying meal. Recommended.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Taste ok. Fried chicken taste quite good. Lamb chop was a bit disappointing.

Totally don‚Äôt recommend! The Korean store owner who take orders really very rude and impatient he only got 5 secs for you , if you ask him more questions he will ignored u and went to take next order . The fried chicken are overrated honestly

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Great place to find authentic hunan cuisines.
Pocket friendly, tasty Indian food is the speciality here. Will visit often hereafter...

Came across this store and thought to give it a try with my friend since it was new. Even though the images on the menu looked promising, we were disappointed because

1. Fried rice was so pathetic that I‚Äôd rather use the money to buy wok hey which is of much better quality. The fried rice tasted bland and the quality of prawns were BAD. Fried rice didn‚Äôt have spring onions but pathetic peas and carrots. There weren‚Äôt large chunks of eggs either.

2. Their wanton soup is of what you can easily get at the coffee shop for $3. The meat fillings were seriously pathetic and there were no seasonings. Soup had too much MSG.

3. Skin of the pan fried buns were too THICK

4. Sausage was supposed to be glazed, but it was very watery and the skin was 90% peeling off. There was no meat in the sausage and it looks dehydrated. My friend felt like she was having starch sausage.

Even though service was prompt, I wouldn‚Äôt  recommend this place because the food quality is THAT bad. I believe there are much better Shanghainese food places out there than this. At this point honestly just go to Ding Tele / DTF.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Super nice Malay Food, will definetely come back again for second round haha

Love their Lok Lok buffet! I always ordered their satay sauce (+$6) as it's very thick and hot, suitable for dipping your lok lok in. The lady boss there is very nice and friendly, don't be surprise if she recommend you on how to eat :)

The staffs are nice too! One of them who just fried the nuggets and chicken wings (SERIOUSLY crispy and tasty) went to every desk to offer them to the customers. I took some of course.

Great service and super friendly staff. Told them our pork jowl is over cooked, too hard and burnt. The manager offered to give us a new plate.

Both my parent and I like to eat their salmon and prawn don (either with mentaiko or without).

Highly recommend this outlet.

Tried the Alacart buffet on a Friday night (need at least 3 pax). The food was really great. I recommend the spicy lala, prawn paste chicken, romantic prawn. The spicy steam fish is amazing too. Give the yam a chance, it‚Äôs amazing! The other desserts are so so only!  Definitely would come back again!

Wendy Tan service is really amazing! Kudos to her and her team for the great service! Birthday boy can dine for free! Would come back here again
One of the best Indian food I had in the recent years in Singapore. Super delicious. Excellent service.

Food so so only when I first visit. Thereafter shopback gave loyality reward and went back for the complimentary reward. Reward indicates no min. Spending for the redemption but they insist you need to purchase a main and not able to redeem with purchase of handroll. They say is shopback issue and not their restaurant.

Not going back there again. If you are not agreeable with shopback T&C of the reward, you shld follow up with them and trash it out. You shld honour it while you trash out with shopback the discrepancy.

Not recommended.

As usual, as great as the brand already is....
‚Ä¢ Very good taste of it's food as usual.
‚Ä¢ The staff is very friendly.
‚Ä¢ Cleanliness is well maintained.
‚Ä¢ Situated in a food court kind of environment, in North Spine plaza, NTU.
‚Ä¢ Does have self-ticketing machines to order whatever you want.
‚Ä¢ Overall a great experience.
The lotus wrapped rice could be more fragrant and the yam paste can be more thicken. Their chicken and abalone dish can be a plus point for events.
Oysters were fresh, very worth the quality. Delicious!

You can tell the food is authentic by the Thai couple running the stall. It's not a restaurant but a self-service stall in a relatively large coffee shop. The food is like that served at road side stalls in Bangkok, which is to say that it's delicious. Prices are very reasonable too. However, be prepared to wait a while for the food, as there's only one cook and business is brisk.

We ordered a three-pax signature dishes set meal, a six-course meal (excluding rice), it was just nice for my family of four (we are not really big eaters). We signed up for their membership ($88) - you will get $50 x 2 vouchers and a whole duck, which is quite worth it!
Pratas were made fresh, and crispy. The fish curry was thick, savoury, tangy and very satisfying. Also, would recommend the soursop drink, very nice. Come here for the good pratas.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Nice place for tim sum in hong kong style. Lots of varieties and freshly made from steam to fried stuffs. Love the congee too!

Weekdays lunch promotions are a steal. Food quality is comparative to most other well established Japanese restaurants.  Prices are competitive and comparable. Its not a super big restaurant. So go there early or make reservations.  You will be surprised by the lunch crowd.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: A good place to chill and enjoy your food. A good ambience. The staff hock seng is very polite and courteous. Keep it up! Things to improve more choices of food would be good :))
Food is alright . Long queue during lunch hour (weekend). They have order in menu beside normal nasi padang style but it open on 12pm onwarda only.

Dishes were 50-50 hit and miss. Hostess at reception seem disorganised and covid precautions need to improve.
Service seems lacking on a busy evening (late to order, missing drink orders) but improved once other tables cleared.

Stumbled on this little stall (located in Orange Point) in this industry park when googling for makan places. It has indeed lived up to its name for the food is charcoal grill. Most of the meat has been sous vide prior to grilling which eventually shorten the waiting time. Taste has been enhanced by the burning charcoal grill. It allow the customer to choose different side such as linguine (with various sauces) or garlic fries. Visited the stall on a Sat evening 6PM, and waiting time is about 10 to 15mins. Service is swift and the staff is polite as well. Price is pretty reasonable. Will visit this stall again for sure.
My favorite place for fish head steamboat. Fish soup, etc etc!

Food: great tasting dishes throughout. What really hit the spot was the pumpkin prawns dish and Dong Bo pork belly. I‚Äôd definitely order it again. On top of regular zi char dishes, they also do interesting ones like black currant ribs, chrysanthemum fried fish.

Ambience: kopitiam Zi char stall lor.

Price: reasonable. Sure, there are cheaper Zi char places, but if you value quality, I‚Äôm sure you won‚Äôt regret forking out a little extra.

with so many other interesting dishes to chow on, I‚Äôm looking forward to my next visit!

Unfortunately the quality has dropped significantly since it's re-opening

Used to be a frequent visitor back in 2020-2021 and the meats and pasta were great then, hence the three stars. However, we eagerly visited them upon hearing that it's re-opened but the pasta was average at best and meat was dry and that is considering an increase in price (which is justifiable in the current market but the drop in quality is not)

Hopefully it can go back to how great it used to be

Awesome noodles which was pretty much close to Malaysia taste.

Worth the queue. Friendly boss too!

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Had their Set A (tasungyuk, jjajangmyun, jjampong and mandoo) and it was delicious! Tangsuyuk was really tasty and best jjampong I have ever eaten. Recommended!

Waited more than 1 hour, ordered claypot rice with side dishes. No sign of side dishes and claypot rice. At least serve the side dishes first la. Cannot even manage the walk in portion. Very disappointed. I suggest you all to order takeaway instead. Very inefficient staff

Grilled meat over charcoal.

Ordered twice on Food Panda and once in-store. Quality has always been consistent.

Favourites: Beef Ribeye, Mushroom, Pork & leeks.

Hands down to Chef Sebastian and the team, my favorite Chinese in Singapore! Love the Sichuan influence and the innovative twist. Wonderful setting as well in the beautiful Duxton Reserve hotel. Highly recommend!

We chanced upon this stall when we were examining our dinner options in this area. While it was newly opened (for less than a month), the quality of food served surpassed our expectations.
We ordered salmon with fresh veg, truffle fries, nuggets (came with a small serving of veg), and a Hawaiian pizza.
The salmon and fries were delicious, nuggets tasted better than the ones you find at fast food outlets, and the pizza was soft and easy to chew, probably due to it being hand-stretched before being cooked.
Prices were reasonable considering the food quality and portions served.
Highly recommended!
Good and tasty one of the nice stall in this AMK food center.
Incredibly tasty and a filling meal at quite a cheap price. Strongly recommend for people who is a meat lover.
Nice vibe,good vibe to chill and relax..food was not bad..environment was good..very relax here..price also affordable.HENG,ONG,HUAT to the boss
Was served by Amy and Sharlene and it was an amazing afternoon at Jack‚Äôs Place! Thank you both for your kindness and positive attitude towards us on a busy Saturday afternoon. ‚ò∫Ô∏è
