I used to enjoy this place very much and came for ramen for many times, but the latest visit really let me down. I ordered set lunch for the first time and it turned out to be a terrible decision: The soup is lukewarm, noodles are soggy, and the chicken char siew is half fat. As a result I was only able to finish less than half noodles and the rest are wasted. I won't go to this place again, so disappointed that the standard dropped trmendously. 1 star is given for the quick service btw.

Crave for Thai cuisine? You don't have to fly to Bangkok to fix your cravings anymore. Just visit ThaiLily at 107 Lorong 1 Toa Payoh and you will find a good selections of authentic Thai food that will satisfy your appetite.
Don't miss out their fish dish promotion. My favourite is the steam fish with thai lime sauce.. currently going at $12.90 instead of the usual $22.
I didn't have time to cook last night so decided to pack the  dinner for my family. And as usual, they enjoyed the food  so much.  Thanks to ThaiLily for the sumptuous dinner!
Spacious and clean restaurant with friendly staff serving good quality vegetarian food. Quiet and cosy setting. Great for family and friends gathering.

The restaurant opened at 8am sharp while the queue is forming. Pretty fast in serving but missed to deliver fully on my order, which is fine as they quickly rectified it. Prata is supper crispy. Coffee and teh tarik a little diluted to our liking. Besides being more oily the overall taste of the prata is great! Btw one of my friend spotted a cockroach running across the seats.

Food was fresh and good. They had 13 soup bases to choose from. Husband had the Teochew Style soup. I had the beef bone soup. We both preferred mine over his.

There is a teatime special promotion - 40% discount. Huge savings off the total bill. Together with the ShopBack Voucher I purchased ($40 for $50 worth) we ended up paying $82 for a bill of $132.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: I have been regular cutomer for past 3 years almost everyday. Very hygienic and best service for every single customer. Highly recommended. Best family restaurant in Jurong East.
Great spot to grab a quick dinner. Food is served very quickly and is pretty decent, considering it‚Äôs just a little shop in a linkway. Prices are very reasonable for the portion size.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Not cheap but not expensive. Prata is not bad. Maggie Mee goreng is good but premises could be cleaner

****

Need to invest in a anti flies light (blue light) too many flies!

The previous store used to sell very good Indian food but not this new owner. Biryani was bland with mutton was scoped from curry mutton., clearly not cooked together. Butter chicken taste artificial.
Nice western food. Will come again.
Trying for the first time, should say that I was really impress by the taste and quality of food. Will definetly go back in future.

Will not return again foods so so..... I visit 3 years ago still can give it a try when I visit again with my family on July 2022 but as I return to this restaurant found that still no change no sell rice. Foods portion too small and expensive $130 for 4 pax. If you are big eater don't go try. If not you can give it a try. Boss and waitress not so friendly only choose guest to talk.

Shiok, simply good.
Noodles done right, taste good with the freshly hand make Fish Cake (deep fried) $ Fish Ball.
Though the soup is kind of salty for me.
Highly recommended.

Cozy place with friendly staff. Quickly seated on a weekday dinner. Back a couple of times to try out different dishes.

My son likes the ribs. Nicely done for a wallet friendly price. Fish was yummy too.

Today, we tried butter chicken burger and seafood aglio olio. Will be back again!
The crispy Sichuan chicken is nice! Good ambience

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Always a go to if near the area, mouth watering dishes at very affordable price. 1 meat 1 vege starts as low as $3+. Often crowded during lunchtime and still have food available  when i have late lunch even at 3+pm. Staff are friendly and helpful. Highly recommended and have been visiting for 5 years.

Very unpleasant dining experience at Lao Hero kitchen on 12 Mar around 6:30pm. , I booked a 6-8 seated round table at the back of the restaurant 2 days prior, with another 5-6 seated square table at the corner as backup in case of the former was occupied on that day. The manager of the restaurant told me she might not be able to secure the round table for me if a group with 6 or more people came before me on that day. But she promised that the 6 seated table at the back corner of the restaurant would definitely be reserved for me. I agreed and a confirmation message was sent to my phone afterwards. However, on the actual day, the round table was taken while the 6 seated table at the corner was deliberately split into tables for 2 and 4. Confused, I approached the staff and she told us to sit at the table near the door. After explaining to her about the reservation 2 days prior, she helped merge the tables together and let us sit there. However, the manager saw this later on and approached the staff, reprimanded her for letting us occupy that table, and demanded us to shift, we told her that we had booked that table and she said she was aware but still demanded us shift to the table near the entry door. My friend was shocked what was happening and demand a explanation and apology. Although we were finally allowed to occupied the table we booked, but no apologies were given at all and the manager was extremely impatient the whole time. I was really appalled and disappointed by their rude service and will definitely won‚Äôt recommend this restaurant.

Laksa was good, hard to find assam broth and ingredients were plentiful and authentic. Came across pineapple slices, mint leaves and fresh onion slices in the soup which added to the taste. Price is pretty affordable as well. Hope they have an option to add-on more meat in future as I like the well marinated chicken slices within too.

One complaint is that their prices on foodpanda is more expensive than in-store even after the 15% pickup discount. I understand they have to pay app commissions but I don't appreciate the lack of business ethics as a customer.

my family is a regular customer here in prata wala jurong point. I would like to thank Ani for always giving us a warm welcome and an excellent service. I always see her tidy up the place and keep the place clean. five thumb‚Äôs up for her.

Been coming here for a while, but in the past month, the food has been way tooooo salty. Suspect chef has long covid anosmia.

The saltiness is obnoxious, such that when u drink the miso soup, it is tasteless because everything is sooooo salty.

Please do something

Have been here several times for the steamboat (fried fish and slice fresh fish). The thick soup base is excellent, all of my guests love it. It's restaurant price but all dishes are served in big portion and services are always good.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Was glad to learn that there is a Indian restaurant around my area. Am a vegetarian. Ordered North Indian thali - meagre rice portion and vegetables; besides paneer did not taste fresh or authentic - more like the instant ready-to-eat type. Also had Badam milk; saw the cook mixing instant badam powder to hot milk and serving. Quite a ripoff. Not stepping there again. Pricey and average taste. I doubt with such standards, they would be able to keep up for long.
Every Sat& Sunday l have my breakfast there or dinner good üëç and nice Roti prata including Tosai very good curry TRY there U will not want to miss it .

Reasonably priced family restaurant with western and local food. Good variety and set meals are value for money. Steak and baked potato is their regular favourites. Grill baramundi in the flavours of the sea is a good seasonal option. New staff Stephy is attentive. Other new service staff does well too.

Love their soy sauce chicken,  char siu and roast pork. Reminds me of the way they serve it in Ipoh -  Cantonese style. Their condiments of chili and ginger oil sauce are also really good. Like in true Cantonese fashion, some of the staff have the attitudes to match (ok, I am stereotyping) and that's the main reason for the low ratings - but I didn't have a problem each time I was there and the taste is just great!
Yummy chicken with ginger sauce. The set menu is quite a good selection, and decent value for the amount of food you get. Make sure to order the XO chilli sauce, it goes well with everything.

Food quality not bad for the price but the soup is not flavourful enough. Bad service. I asked for help as it‚Äôs my first time. The staff only pointed the ordering machine to me and did not inform me that I have to collect my drink at separate counter. When I collected my ramen, I asked where‚Äôs my tea, then the kitchen staff shouted loudly telling me to go collect from the front. They shouted as if it‚Äôs my fault for not knowing and they did not say clearly which part of the ‚Äúfront‚Äù! During my short meal there, I witnessed same treatment was given to another customer. Such horrible service!
Food is good. Wings are extra crispy. Long queue always.  Be prepared for the wait because its worth the wait.
Price is reasonable. Most of the ramen is about $5. No GST no SVC. Taste is nice and worth trying
The service is extremely bad. Food is atrocious, every dish comes out not even hot. Worse kind of food I‚Äôve ever had in life. Highly not recommended.

We had the steam fish with lemon. Tongan cream seafood soup , kailan with garlic plus red Ruby as dessert: all the dishes were tasty. I wld certainly come back again. Also the price is very very reasonable.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Very shiok spicy, chicken was tender and rice was very very fragrant! The ikan billis was too hard for me though. Highly recommended!

This has got to be one of the best congee stalls I‚Äôve tried so far. Thick porridge. Chock full of quality ingredients. Costs almost twice as much as your typical hawker centre porridge but I guess you get what you pay for.
One of the Best hawker-style Western Foods I've tasted so far!

Re-opened with a new menu.  Main courses and desserts were great along with the service.  We had dinner and the prices were reasonable considering the comfort, view and proper restaurant service.  Really great addition to NTU if you need some cool comfort after a long day of study/work.
Fresh ingredients. Only problem was the wait time for table. But I guess is normal for peak hours. Will definitely come back again.

A hidden gem in the AMK neighbourhood provides nice steak. The steak approximately 250g with a great thickness and worth for money. The grilled chicken also taste good and the portion of it was great.

Good food though a bit on the salty side.. service also can give 4.5 stars out of 5.. but the last month I went, I saw they did not have a separate container or bowl to keep the scoop when serving the fried rice dish. Instead the scoop was placed beside the bottom of the pot. Which I think is not so hygienic, given the fact that the fried rice has been on a burner before. Hope the restaurant can take not please.
Affordable nasi padang and other dishes, fast service
Good portions. Value for money. And quick service. Loved the beef biryani

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Ever since they changed their store head, the taste is totally not right, starting from half cooked noodles (which both me and my mum couldn‚Äôt finish) to the soy sauce chicken having a mild curry flavour, I had really Nothing much to say apart from some decent soup of the day rather then having ghee water soup... they used to have very good soy sauce chicken which we always ordered a full chicken... what happened?

Today's 2 Nov 2020 and they are still serving the fish for $12.90. We ordered the tomyam fish as in our picture and loved it. Its like having 2 dishes in one LOL.

The green curry has pineapples in it that gives it a sweet taste, unlike the other Thai places. We like.

The pork kailan had very few pieces of roast pork though. Wished there were more.

Total for the 3 of us was $31.90 with no drinks.
Great food! Price is affordable too. Highly recommend the tandoori chicken - really tender and flavourful.
Brilliant food and service, comfortable seating. Enjoyed the Mutton briyani, Naan, Palak Paneer.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Decent full set meal. Very delicious, hearty meal for $9.50. Fairly reasonable. The potato , mock meat masala and payasam was the highlight. Well done guys. Keep it up!
Having dinner here actually not bad the food was perfectly fresh and taste good a good place for family and friend meeting place

One of my worst dining experience. Will never return back anymore. Food portion is not worth for the price. Horrible staff service, when being approached by the staff rude manners and not being understanding.
Food is really good... will go back again...
The best prata ever! The fish curry and nasi goreng ayam is superb!
The food is worth the price. the service is always quick. You get Indian food too - dosa, chapathi, idly.
Per person Ala carte free flow of ordered dishes.  Try the fried Soon Hock fish. It is very good
Tried Tom Yum clear soup. Doesn't taste very impressive and can be rather expensive~
Chicken chop was awesome. Generous portions!
The food is good & tasty. I do patronise it every week. It's a bit pricy, but food  is good.

who knew scrambled eggs and potato crisps would go so well with malatang? this is a bowl that i‚Äôll remember for a while to come; terrible location putting me off but i hope to come back again at some point in the future

One of my favorite branch. Food is great and value for price.
Must order Salmon Belly very good. Geso karaage is huge. I enjoyed the mentaiko sushis too. Everything we tried was nice. However, menu changed and there's no chasiu rice anymore.
FREE ice water, Wasabi and soy sauce available on request.  Generally not crowded on weekday lunch. Spend more than $20 to get a coin to play claw machine for ice cream.

Update: new item like steam osyter is a must try!
The taste is good, the price is good, and the service attitude is too bad
Very fresh sashimi! Prices are reasonable too. Will come again :)

I have never tried the food in Anson before. But the food in this restaurant had unique food that aren't commonly found in Singapore.

They also bake their pastries fresh everyday. My family loves the traditional pastries.

Rojak with crispy cracker taste good, but because they use a bowl, all the rojak sauce sank to the bottom and it turned out super salty.

The rest of the food were great, I love the Anson Special chee cheong fun, very silky and smooth. Will definitely try other flavour next time.

Overall, nice ambience and great food!

Food is really good and service crew is very friendly! like Otoro Aburi Handroll and Black Truffle Cold Udon the most üòçüòç Lamb Ribs is average but Spicy Baby Corn is quite good üòÅ *Bonus* they gave my friend a little birthday surprise when we're about to leave ü•∞ thank you for taking note on my reservation comment that I almost forgot ü§£
Nice setup for a veg restaurant. Food is good and I like their variety  of soup .
Located on the second floor of Amara Hotel, this restaurant serves enjoyable SzeChuan food. The spiciness of the food is moderate, and the starters are quite good.
reasonable prices and fast service! food is delicious too.
Food is good

Extremely disappointed at the experience I had today, went there at around 2pm and was told by one staff that waiting time was about 3 to 4 hours and another that it was 4 to 5 hours. That seemed reasonable enough so I came back after 4 hours and asked for an update for how much longer it would take for my turn, the staff went to check at the computer and told me that it would be about an hour more. So I came back after another hour and this time I was told by another staff that it was likely that even if I waited till closing time, my turn to enter would not come.  I don't mind waiting for hours for the food but being told that it would take 4 to 5 hours and 1 hour more after I asked for an update, I would never have thought that I would not even be able to eat. In the first place, the management should have known that having this opening promo would bring about an overwhelming number of customers and should have set a maximum eating time like how genki sushi does it. I asked the staff why a maximum eating time was not imposed, the staff replied in a rhetoric manner asking me if I want a 30min time limit or a 1 hour time limit and told me they cannot control how long the people stay there to eat. I was also told that I should have estimated the waiting time myself, but I was already told by the staff that the waiting time was about 4 to 5 hours. Additionally, by 2pm the staff should have already been able to realise that they have given out too many queue numbers judging from the trends since opening in the morning and should have cut the queue number collection. My number was in the 200s for the 2 seater tables, and it was no where near my queue number near closing time, and to make it worse the last queue number is  almost 400. I am not sure how they estimated so badly the waiting time. The management was really awful and I am very disappointed.
To summarise:
1. not imposing a maximum eating time.
2. given an extremely wrong estimation of waiting time such that I was not even able to eat by the end of the day
3. not cutting off collection of queue number when it was very apparent that they had given too many queue numbers.
4. staff making it seem like it was my fault for not estimating the waiting time myself when they already told me that it would be about 4 to 5 hours

I would give 0 stars if I could, this is really unacceptable
Best Filipino food in the country

The chye poh kueh tiao was an eye opener, very unique taste! We also loved the braised pork bao and salted kampung chicken! Sambal kangkong was a flop, too watery... Overall better than an average zichar place but price is also higher... Will be back to try other dishes!

Today we eat the original ramen together with my husband at Jurong outlook, taste so wonderful. I finished till last drop of soup . Can say is the best ramen I have ever had so far. Love the bamboo shoots plus the slice mushroom, the combination is just too excellent, I can't have enough of it. Will come back again next week

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Disappointing. This place was good and had recommended it to many people but the standard has dropped significantly. Jjajangmyeon didn't taste right - lack the sweet and salty balance - just tasted like a bowl of noodles with no purpose. Tangsuyuk tasted like how it was then but the sauce was too liquid like dipping into water. Itaewon Jjajang down the street might be a better consideration for those who want authentic Korean jjajangmyeon and tangsuyuk.

Not much variety only fried carrot cake, oyster eggs, char kway Teow, claypot rice, Assam laksa n prawn noodles.
Tried the fried kway Teow, Assam laksa n prawn noodles.. I still prefer the one at Jurong point
Quite fast despite the longer qyeue. Fish is fresh and tasty. Had wanted to try the tempura but had to wait 30 minutes. Shows he cooks it fresh.
Friendly staff! The food was good, will definitely come again :)
Not as good as expected, the food really so so.

I like their plain chee cheong fun texture. French toast loved by my boy. Go off peak and the wait will be more bearable. We went like brunch hours. Not 5 stars because ËæìÂú®har gao is disappointing.
Food and drinks reasonable. Loves the food yummy and spicy.  Will come again with friends.
They will test your patience. Even though it was not that busy on this Saturday night 10 pm they kept me waiting 15 minutes for my banana prata untill I finish my teh tareh..
we had italian herb chicken fried rice and tomato and egg fried rice, large portions, tasty and value for money.

Everything here is simple & basics. The stall is simple, the food looks simple, but the taste is of quality. The basis of the rice, every grain is moist & soft but it doesn‚Äôt lumped together (it takes skill to achieve that!). Overall, Great!
Excellent service. The staff were friendly and accommodating

Tried their new year set dinner. Taste and freshness were good but the serving was so small it was almost funny at times. Not that affordably priced considering the serving size. The food was served extremely slowly too making the entire dining experience disappointing. The deep fried brinjal w pork floss (not part of the set) was good though.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
1st Visit To This Food Centre... Alot Of e Stalls Are Not Open On A Wednesday Weekday Around 11+ 12pm. However, There's A Number Of Stalls w Queues For Lunch Crowd Still... üòä
A Nostalgic Taste Of Kway Chap!! Can Try If You Are A Kway Chap Lover... I Don't Really Take Intestines, But Theirs Are Indeed Well Served I Would Say~

We used to always visit this place when it was at Khatib.  It's moved to AMK for 4 years but we always come here once in a while as a treat. We know the owner and the food is good. I didn't take photos of the food today (too famished), BUT here's a pic of their awesome brownie with vanilla ice-cream!

Very interesting, fun Dinning experience,
Sushi üç£ very  nice . price  from $1.8 a salmon Sushi.
Bring your children come and experience a unique fun dinning .

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: First time trying takeout shop, normally is having at their physical shop dine in, food standard compare to dine in I feel better here at takeout shop. The taste is fresh surprisingly. Price wise is cheaper also for some item, 10 pcs salmon sushi for $5.00. What a steel. Looking for a takeaway meal this shop is Highly recommend to go buy.
Omelette is delicious with chicken meat and preserved radish (i think). Tom yum soup is not too spicy but still flavourful. Will come back and try other dishes next time.

Waiting time is almost an hour on a weekend lunch time. Recommended to go at around 2:30-3pm where there are lesser crowd.
Sushi standards were mediocre, for the price I would prefer other express sushi place or Ichiban Sushi instead. The butter soyu is a tat too sweet. Maybe it‚Äôs newly open, they always forgot the customers order. I overheard 2 tables with missing orders, same as us when we visit, orders forgotten but were marked as Completed in the system.
The seating is pretty small, I guess petite size people will feel more comfortable.

Rich, sweet and creamy mee rebus. Easily one of the best in Singapore. Ayam is soft and tender, and the satay peanut sauce gives it such a delightful experience overall. It‚Äôs a very rich and filling meal overall, so prepare your stomach.
üëç

Great food but slightly expensive.

Tom Yum Prawn Soup is very aromatic and spicy and was the best amongst the order.

Red curry is also very good and not too spicy with amazing flavours.

Pandan chicken wasn‚Äôt good as the meat was chewy and not succulent. Had to leave it.

One of the best neighborhood western food stall. Followed them from three locations in Toa Payoh. Son of the owner is now running the show and very customer oriented. I loves their butter whipped potatoes besides their lovely main courses.
Lousy quality good and yet overpriced
Good food at reasonable prices. Most impressed by the baked flower crabs. Very good har Cheong gai too. Salted veg fish stew is nice, but cost ~$100.
Ordered for 6 pax today, food is good üëçüèª chicken‚Äôs the highlight of course ü§£ bean sprout tasted a little raw, could be cooked more thoroughly. Portion is good and price is fair üòä

The food was really good and the staff was super friendly!!! We had the Australian Wagyu platter, which was recommended by the staff and it was really tender and delicious. The only downside was the wait time, which was understandable as they have very limited seating and the tables were full when we came. Next time we will try the Double Ribeye platter, which was another recommendation by the staff. However, I suggest booking on their website or whatsapp them as walk ins may not guarantee a open table. The staff were nice enough to take our numbers and called us when they had an open table. Overall it was a 10/10 experience!

The food here is really good! We came here on a Saturday for lunch and the ambience at the park was nice. Their service staff are also attentive and easy to get their attention. Would recommend their wagyu beef don ($30+) and chawanmushi. Nice place to spend a bit more money and chill vibes.

Near the carpark too so it's easy to get to.

Would come again!

I had previously patronised this place to try their Penang Fried Kway Teow and it didn't taste authentic.

Just 2 weeks ago, my parents returned and were giving praises on the food - tasty and had the charred aroma coming from wok.

Skeptical but didn't mind trying. Truly the food were great, with portions being decent and can be shared by two(not a big eater). My family of 3 visited on Friday at 630pm which was already fairly crowded but managed to get a table. Come any later, you may need to wait around.

We  ordered:
1. Penang Fried Kway Teow ($5.50)
-little moist and spicy level is acceptable

2. Crispy Sheng Mian ($5.50)
-
3. Thai Style Tofu ($6.00~)
- light on the batter, crispy on the outside but soft on the insight.
- appetizing to kick start your meal

4. Sweet & Sour Fish ($9.90 promo)
- nicely fried and fish is quite meaty

I have been eating their lor mee for decades, and absolutely love the thick, flavorful broth. Their marinated egg is also very delicious, and it shows just how much time and effort has gone into preparing the ingredients. A multiple award holder at local TV food variety shows - it is a must try for all lor mee fans! We paid S$4.50 for this bowl.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Good customer service and reasonable pricing

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Nice place and nice food. Everything (soup, marinade, sauces) was the right combination of spicy, sweet, sour, salty. Can tell that they are a little short handed but it didn‚Äôt affect the food or service in any way. üëçüèª

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Supported them from last time 3 years ago in pasir ris all the way till I moved to toa payoh.

This time round unfortunately have to give a 1 star review as they decided to change their free flow ice cream to chargeable. Went there most of the time for free flow ice cream. Now no more so have to look for other mookata place.........

The most value for money ramen in SG! $6.90 bowl was amazing - soup was thick and delicious without being too salty or MSG ish, noodles were QQ and char siew was decent and not too thin.

Didnt have a picture as i gobbled down my bowl haha

Would highly recommend!

Expensive, bad service and bad food. $5.50 for a packet of soya sauce chicken with mostly bones. What a cheating eatery! I bought this for my child and ended up there was very little edible part. Service was prompt but without smile, bordering on rude. I was a regular many years ago but since the change of boss, it‚Äôs bad service and bad food.
They offer delicious Malay food, the sambal chili is homemade by the boss.

Wide varieties of Thai food selections. Nice ambience with aircon. They sell liquor too.
Mixed meat platter is mooping, lemongrass chicken and grilled pork neck.
Seabass with garlic is not tough.
Fried papaya salad with soft shell crab is special.
Fried omelette with crab meat is very flavourful.
We should have order some non fried dishes to balance the meal.
A place worth visiting. They have points accumulation system so make sure you order through qr code to have the points accumulation. We wasn't told and order taken down by waitress but boss Jeremy is good to offer he will settle it backend for us.

Food is good, but unfortunately preparations for take out in general are very tardy, and they may cause waits for over an hour. 30+ minute to over an hour wait are not exclusive cases either, and happens more often than I'd like

Staff are very nonchalant. They tend to ignore orders until customer(s) assert some form of urged communication
This stall used to be rasa sayang which has moved to another part of amk. Standard of food has dropped drastically since then. Go to Vincent's located at nearby hawker centre for better food.
Good customer service. Loved the ambience & ofcourse their food as well!

Was introduced by my sis that their porridge very nice and alots of varieties.
Mainly porridges but have some side dishes too.

We ordered with set (YouTiao & SoyMilk), the portion quite big, n their porridge more ‚Äúthick‚Äù so easy to get full, most impt is yummy üëç
Price is reasonable too.

The shop is in the middle of others restaurant, first timer maybe need some time to look for it. Shop design is simple but is ok, I guess their main point is provide good & delicious food.

Read the good reviews and always enjoy the food and no issue with the service until today. I was there with family at 2.00pm but was shouted by a staff who claimed that last order is at 2pm., she addressed us as HALO , HALO when we were about to walk into the restaurant, saying that last order closed, but the lady at the reception was nicer, approached us and told us to come at 3pm for the buffet.  The staff need to be trained on how to approached the customer in a nicer way than to behave like she is in the market place,  Please educate your staff.
Can't go wrong with a good ol burrito bowl :-) Food's great, and thank you Kelvin and team for the warm welcome always!
Food looks nothing like the photos. It does not taste great either - certainly not for the price! Setting is also so-so

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Go till stall owner saved my hp no. after I make reservation last few times. And even gave me discount voucherüòÇ..... Where to find! So far,  best Mookata after few diff places I went & ate. Still prefer this one.

Nice food and attentive staff.
Well organized after renovation.

Comfy food during raining day.. I ordered the original and the soup broth is clear and nice. Doesn‚Äôt taste much MSG.. ordered a set come with a drink, an egg and a dessert. The prawn is fresh, shelf removed for you and left the head and tail. Give it a try!
Must try indian food üòÑ
Great place for meals. Convenient location. Few minutes walk to Ang Mo Kio train station and shopping mall Ang Mo Kio hub. Usually not crowded.

O....This Thai restaurant foods is marvellous...Price also very reasonable...Must try...
Felt $$ n foods are better than Nakhon or Ah Loy Thai .

Blown away by the smell of the fried rice when i opened the box, it smells so nice.

Taste is just as good as other famous fried rice places.

A pity this place is not as famous, will come back again to try the other menu.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Their Mutton dum briyani is great!

Delicious. Can custom your own donburi, choose your main, rice/noodles, sides and sauce. Ordered Saba fish donburi. Very nice. Comes with free salmon soup. Salmon soup is also very nice. Will come back again. üòã
Food was good.

At first I though they serve French cuisine by their name but they are actually kind of western & Filipino fusion. Their Filipino food are nice and reasonable pricing but their western and pasta menu are much more expensive though they are also rather good. They have live singing on some days which I don't really enjoy as they are simply too loud for such a small setting.
Good food at reasonable prices in a HDB neighborhood and with better interiors that are comparable to restaurants.
Nice Zhi char food. Good for big group
Clean and comfortable to dine here.  Extremely friendly and efficient staff.

Fried rice (Chicken /pork) are good. The seafood fried noodles has a lovely  side of crispy and creamy mix to it.

The Deer meat curry and rice is  a good try as well .but would suggest to go for the pepper mix rather than sambhal..

All in all a good place to have chill out with drinks and food...Value for money tooüí≤üòÉ
Was impressed that they served very good food. But sadly the staff did not provide good service, which makes the overall experience slight bad. 4 stars for the food not service.
The plain and egg prata were good. The exterior was crispy yet the in inside was soft and chewy. However, the fish curry was on the salty side otherwise it is good.

Poached eggs are cold

Torched Mentai is also cold

Whole place no aircon

Serve customer with burnt fries

Never again!
Good but not 24hrs

Ordered the Tonkotsu Ramen ($6.90). The Ramen is ‚ÄúQ‚Äù in texture. The broth is thick and filled with Collagen, simply put: On Point. For the char siew, the size was decent, not too thin. However as with most reviews, the char siew was tasteless. Overall, for the price, the portion and the broth was pretty value for the money.

What a cute find in Buangkok! The menu looks super tasty and the dishes served up didn‚Äôt disappoint. Highlights were the grilled spicy sliced fish, mapo tofu, fried eggplant and that sweet and sour pork (in a nostalgic batter from our childhood) made for a very moreish dinner. Prices are great, peppercorns are numbing and we will be back soon to eat the rest of the menu.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Chicken was tender and flavourful. Chilli very spicy but shiok la. Recommended!
The taste of the Chee Cheong Fun is delicious, soft, and smooth. It surprised me when I took the first bite. But the taste of the pigskin is so so...
food was horrible!

Aftermath;
Food- superb ü§©ü§©
Service- above average (considering it‚Äôs late night 11:12pm)
Ambiance- average (just 3mins walk away from mrt station)

Overall- great for everyone who‚Äôs looking for values for money food to stuff your big belly üòÅ

Have no issue in communicating with the staffs in Chinese. The food are Averagely good. The clay pot chicken have many tiny bones , not sure if it‚Äôs due to frozen chicken or overcook. The garlic chicken is garlic-ky.. can see many garlics in there haha. Meanwhile, have to wait awhile for food to be ready, not sure why but still within acceptable range.

This restaurant offers several value for money set meals. Due to  the profile of most residents in this neoghbourhood the restaurant also offers set menu for senior citizens. We tried the pork knuckle and found it tasty. Portion is huge even for 2 to share that we had to pack it home.

This is a really bad sushi to be honest .  Cheap ingrediants and selling it over price except for the ebiko the rest are cheap ingrediants like egg,cucumbe, crab meat . The sushi rice is quite sweet . Salmon is cut as thin as a panty liner . Whats worst ‚Ä¶ Soy sauce is not japanese soy sauce .. its some breakfast egg soy sauce/cooking soy sauce ‚Ä¶ Would highly not recommend ‚Ä¶

I and friends of mine went here at lunch time at the weekend.
We ordered famous Xiao Long Bao, Steamed Vegetarian Dumplings, Pan-fried dumplings and the red bean pancake with soup and beer. ‚Ä¶
not bad, affordable pricing. their homemade sauce is nice and goes well with the food. will come back again
The egg and onion prata is not bad, and I like the curry. However the mee goreng is too wet.

Tried this after seeing good Google reviews and boy was it spot on. Operated by a Thai couple in a modest Balestier road coffeeshop stall, there‚Äôs a wide variety of food on the menu. We had to do takeaway during this period but it didn‚Äôt affect the quality of the food. We particularly loved how flavourful the Tom Yum was, and it was packed full of ingredients such as fish slices and squid. The basil chicken wasn‚Äôt too spicy but it managed to pack a nice punch, especially when I had it with the Tom Yum. The pandan chicken was succulent. Unassuming Thai comfort food. Overall a great experience and we will be back for more.

The pictures don‚Äôt do justice to the food as they were taken from a video we shot via screen grab (forgot to take photos).
This is a nice place to check out in NTU when students are looking to treat themselves to some good food

Their staff really fussy, force you to pay for the 30cents container and claim due to food hygiene & can not mix with other food together. What a not environment move friendly! You are creating more rubbish in our tiny island!

Furthermore, the food is not up to standard taste. Their popiah not nice at all. You can tell from the picture. The skin has melted.

Rojak so so only.

Will not come back again in future.

Located in a quiet neighbourhood, this stall can be found in the coffeeshop under a multistorey carpark. The #ChickenChop in #MushroomSauce is average, like its coleslaw but the onion rings is a failure. Might not return again.
Their tomyum seafood soup is pretty good! Ordered for takeaway.

Our 1st visit (09/1/22) as nearby and early enough to get a table. We're pleased with the place and foods, but the music bit too loud for the small space. Hope they turn volume down a notch after reading this and keeping both standards cum prices. Less a star for the loud music.
Overpriced and underwhelming food. Have to wait forever for your order even when the place is called express. Save your money and time from this restaurant. Do not recommend at all.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content:
I have visited many times , food is good but the service is not good.
They will make you wait for long time just to b order the food.

Egg tart was too sweet
Hor fun was too oily

The rest are not bad

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: 1 pkt (1 Veg + 1 chicken) and 1 pkt (1 Veg + 1 chicken + 1 Fish) Total: $14.90. Taste ok but not sure this is considered economical...
Food was ok.. but service was super slow

it would be an understatement to say this place is the best place for authentic, cheap and absolutely, mind blowing Japanese food. the staff here are world class and the decor feels comfortable yet not overwhelmingly upscale. the place is kept spotless and well mantained. the restaurant itself is joined with another right beside it essentially doubling the menu and giving you the option of grilled yakitori or udon, ramen soba and Don and much much more signature drinks and side dishes. would give 6 stars if I could. 11/10
Elahe is the best place for me and family to dine in...most of the menu i have tried and its very super sedap.
Mee Rebus was very tasty. Chicken Satay was generous, succulent and satisfying. On top of that, prices were very affordable. Thumbs Up!!!
Cheapest Nasi Lemak @$1/- a packet that comes with ikan bilis & egg. If you want a light breakfast or for tea time, have it & you'll never regret.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content:
(Translated by Google) Ô∏è

(Original)
üôÇüôÇüôÇ

Second visit. Food is nice and the less salty/oil makes the dishes we ordered seems more healthy. The fish maw soup comes full of fish maw and other ingredients. The fried baby squids are crispy. The chicken wrapped in cabbage is good.

One of the waiter stood so close and knocked me without apologising. The chair was wet, had to swap a clean one.
Affordable with below average food.
Raspberry drink should be removed from Menu.
Plating needs additional training. Plate was so big that two of it took the whole table space.
Utensils full of water marks and some stubborn food stains.

Chicken was dry, salad with citrus dressing a very safe approach.
Pork heavily covered with black pepper, could season it better.

Difficult to decipher why the waitress kept wanting to clear the plates while we are still on the dishes.

Asked for bill twice (was off peak) and the waitress told us it's paid. Out of integrity I asked the third time.
Billed and never would I dine here again.

Not recommended. Dine at your own risk.
Great food great ambience. The food are tasty and delicious that we foresee we will visit here again! Service was excellent also. Highly recommend!
It's MacDonald's, the same one everywhere. Qs can be a bit chaotic during mealtimes, otherwise it's all good. There is no air-conditioning but plenty of seats.

One star is for the train service. Lol. Salmon sashimi itself is like frozen thawed food, not fresh. California Roll like had a train wrecked upon arriving. Chicken Nanban had so much dough on it, the worst among other japanese restaurants in Jurong Point. Fried squid tentacles, i dont mind it was double fried but when served it is not even hot on the inside..omg.

Food is ok and reasonably priced, but service needs much improvement. Service staff Amy portioned our food out of our sight behind a pillar, so we don't even know if she indeed served us all the fish or all the noodles or all the orh nee etc.

She also ignored our feedback that our dishes were not served in the order we'd like. Noodles were ready as the 5th course when it should have been the 7th. We told her about it, she acknowledged and read out the remaining courses from our ordering chit and brought the big plate of noodles away so we thought she served it to another table. But turns out she just brought it behind the pillar to portion it out for all of us.

Also, a few staff served us at least 2 rounds of diluted-until-cannot tea until we asked to change the tea bag. Did they not see that the liquid they were pouring into our cups was clear and not at all brown?

And not sure what the staff were rushing for since we left about 30min to closing so it can't be for a next seating...my sister's plate and cutlery were cleared just as soon as she bit into a piece of pork, she didn't even have the chance to use her chopsticks to shift the meat to a more comfortable position in her mouth because the chopsticks were already gone as soon as she put them down on her plate.
Authentic Thai cuisine taste! Phad Thai seems to be a bit healthier so it‚Äôs on the less flavourful side. Tom Yam was awesome. Portions for veg was larger as well.
Some staff is rude. Place so small. Can be considered for take away maybe.
Great sushi for all times

Comfortable air con seating area.

Outrageous extra charge for Diet Pepsi! Destroyers of public health
Good olive rice with so many veggies to choose. Nice option for vegetarians.

I would say of the mala xiangguo I ate in the northern part of SG, this stall in Central SG is decent. Ordered small spicy, with rice, came up to 13.40. The ma and la is quite on point for small spice. Though I only gave 4 stars because the xiang is missing.
Sirloin steak is inedible. The entire thing is full of nothing but tendons.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Soup is almost tasteless. Meat normal, marinate not well enough. Spicy chicken cannot make it. A bit shock at d amount had to pay at cashier. No order list to verify.
food taste It very like Thai food in Thailand sell, but waitress services are bad

This is a disgrace to Malaysia street food.
Especially the service standard.
And the "no say" attitude in your preference of chilli or not. Because there is only 1 type set by the stall, simply this is their way which you have to accept.
Char Kuay Teow suck!

Stands out as an air conditioned prata place at the corner of AMK hub. It can get a bit chaotic, and yes you can probably find a cheaper place to get your prata fix - but in a hot day this serves an oasis.
Family friendly restaurant. Food is nice and hot even when it's crowded. Affordable glasses of wine to pair with steaks.

French toast was good.
Others r ok.
Pretty decent and crispy prata. Just that the curry was abit too watery. A little pricey but it was still ok.
Must try Nasi whenever I drop-by that area.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Service poor. Priority given to take away orders. No team coordination within workers. I hope owner take swift action into this matter as it frustrates customers to wait for their food for 20minutes.
The waiter enthusiasmÔºåthe is good
Great customer service, average Thai food pricing! It's a must try, it's so fresh and authentic!

Worst experience ever. I placed the order at 18:09 and now it is 18:58 and I finally get my food after times and times inquiries. It seems that my order was missing in McDonald‚Äôs system.
The funny thing is that the aunties at the counter just asked me to buy food at other stalls even though I had paid in McDonald‚Äôs. They said they were busy and no one tried to get my food ready. Then I requested to get refund and gave up the food. But they just refused and said how can I get a refund after I paid the money. (Totally wired logic)
Luckily, I am not in a hurry to do something today, and another auntie finally stood up, collected my food and beverage, and gave them to me (the food in my order is just ordinary ones, why took so long to prepare). But who wants to waste time on these tiny things, right?
Lesson: don‚Äôt order at McDonald‚Äôs in NTU if they already have a lot of orders to handle.

Super upset and angry with the drink stall chinese lady. Paid $34.80 for my drinks but the actual bill was $22.60 because they forgotten about there was a discount for the beer. Just because i use OCBC paynow, the chinese lady said they cannot refund me in cash of the differences but ask me to buy drinks from the stall instead. I insisted for the difference and she keep refusing until the guy from the zi char stall came by to help and told the chinese lady to refund me in cash. And i told the zi char guy that‚Äôs what i ask for and the chinese lady suddenly came to me and change her story and say (in chinese) ‚Äú is not that i don‚Äôt want to give you back the difference, but i was just trying to explain to you.‚Äù This chinese lady super good at twisting her story! Was really fuming üò§

The food is beyond amazing and staff are great and friendly
Reasonably priced and great ambience
Good taste startedong time ago at opp Malay mosque now near Amk Interchange

Great food at affordable prices. Ordered a Ribeye and it was cooked beautifully. The garlic butter Merlot sauce is incredibly creamy with a good amount of flavor that goes well with the steak.

Very highly recommend.
Very good service. The quality of the Lok Lok is just ok. Would recommend the satay, satay sauce and thai fish cake.
Limited variety. South Indian food is the main attraction. Less waiting time. Located near lakeside MRT. Popular among indians around.
food is nice la but $15 for 8 slice of meat like abit scam city sia. go 1nce can alr

Although abit messy but taste really good for Penang prawn noodle. Very strong flavour though abit thirsty after eating.

Will wan to try lor mee next time

The service staff tried their best but this outlet is obviously understaffed. An hour in the queue and a long wait for food.

If you plan to come during dinner time, you may need to buffer 1.5hours waiting time.
How I order in grab food. I wanted to change address within 5 secs but they didn‚Äôt let me to. And they cheated my 14.10 . They delivered to wrong address.

My honest advice to the two young guys from fried kway teow and penang prawn mee stall, if this work is really that difficult for you, you can actually stop working here and move on
Terrible attitude against all customers
1. keep talking bad about customer in front of them
2. not even bother to take order from customer (pity the boss)
3. keep messing up with customer orders, customer need to wait another round because of the mistake (I don't understand because all customer ordering fried kway teow only, and it is like just 3 to 4 orders, but you still can make mistake?) plus you did wrong but still showing attitude to customer? (pity the customers)
4. one of the customer in front of me asked for non spicy, the staff from penang prawn mee shout very loud saying that can not choose no spicy, but when i get mine, it is not spicy at all (just because you want to do all orders in one go, you tell customer can not choose?)

At last, the food really so so only, so no more next time
No reason to get yourself insulted there for a food that not delicious and not to say very cheap
Limited dinning table is only available there.they take so many times for food deliver to dinning table to customers becoz of crowd.approximately 30 dinning seated there.thank u guys
Crowded and decent Cantonese food. Lots of promotions available. Service decent despite big crowd.

Nasi lemak, I ate before they gave me fish head. When they have not enough fish so they cut the fish into half to served other customers. Don't buy their sardines curry Puff inside all onions and bit of mince sardines. Service not so good one of them so rude and stuck up.

Poor service. Pricey. Ok food.

Imagine waiting a long time queuing even though there's only two in the line only to get your order forgotten.

Ate here multilple times hoping the service would be different, yet each time it never fails to disappoint.

Tried penang laksa, ipoh hor fun and anson special chee cheong fun. Laksa taste ok lack of prawn paste. Chee cheong fun is not up to my expectation as uts kind of bland and dry. The hor fun taste normal. Like the home made soya bean milk, quite tasty and not too sweet.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Excellent service,  affordable price food is fresh their spicy chilli is super hot  i love the tomyum  staff very friendly but need to wait for table if no reservation  worth waiting 5 +1 stars  ******

Will not patronise again. Delivery was late which is ok but at least have the decency to apologise when we called to check. At last, the food arrived 39 mins later and guess what. We ordered 2 combos and 3 a la cartes but was missing of 1 combo (calamari and 1 drink). The service is just wow.
Me n my wife love this place. Abit ex but restaurant standard that doesn't disappoint.

Dining environment is pleasant. Ordered Rosti n Sausage and make it a set with mushroom soup and root beer. Added a onion rings basket. Overall food is good and value for money. However root beer is served 3/4 full and scoop of ice cream is small. Hope that this can be improved.
Best masala tea in Singapore Johor n Riau

Consistently good Chinese food! The Samsui chicken with a generous portion of ginger and lettuce wraps is a must have. Also good is their selection of soups and claypot rice dishes. I really liked the steamed minced pork with water chestnut as well.

It was not a pleasant experience.  The sushi was soggy. The rice had the texture of porridge.  It tasted like the sushi was frozen and then defrosted in the microwave.  The staff was unpleasant and did not seem to care very much. One of the male staff who looks like the owner/manager walked in and out of the kitchen without a mask.  We will not come back.
Service was slow. Ordered and waited for 30 minutes when the other tables already had their order served. As if they needed to plant the vege before cooking them üôÑ
Best place to have breakfast.. nice tea and don't miss to taste free biscuits..

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: The best place for chicken rice in my opinion. My kids love this place. All their dishes are good. Our fave are the roasted chicken rice, hot plate beancurd, baby kailan, fu rong omelette.. somehow this outlet's food is far better than the Northpoint outlet.
Food was good! It‚Äôs a hidden gemüòç Loved the Hak chiong gaiüòç
Understated from the outside; all substance in the menu. One of the best finds in Singapore.

I was there on Sat with two other friends. We ordered spinach in superior stock, golden cereal prawn, salted kampong chicken, a chilli crab with 6 mantous and orh nee with ginko nuts. The place was under-staffed and was packed with customers, hence we waited quite a while (1) before being directed to the reserved table and (2) for our dishes to be served. The food was average, nothing exceptional.
That egg. Crisp ring of skin and runny yolk. Every dish came over well cooked with balanced seasoning.
fried kway teow and claypot rice stall  attitude problem. look like i owe them alot of money.

Have not tried other dishes but pad Thai with prawns was a great disappointment. Prawns are very tiny and the texture and taste of pad Thai is not the usual flavoured ones. For the price, it is not worth it.
Truly authentic food served here and simply delicious.. Enjoyed by my mum and myself.. The family is really nice to their customers too. Kudos...

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
I would got to say this place is really a value for money if you are into eating loads and is tight on budget. They are running a promo at $35 for 2 person (Eat-all-you-can).

Try it!

The downside is that the place is severely understaffed. But the people did their best to help you as much as possible. So kudos to them! :)

This is the best Push Cart DIM SUM buffet that I ever had in Singapore. The restaurant looks exactly like Yam Cha place. We have 1.5hrs to gets the foods and even the waitress will come to you for the last orders, so that you can order your favourite dishes as a happy ending! I like their Xiao Long Bao,Golden Custard Pau, Har Kao,Siew Mai,Paper Wrapped with Chicken,chicken claws with spices,fried spring roll and crispy shrimps dumpling. I love their dessert especially the Red Bean Paste and banan pastry and Sweet Almond longan.The price is $67.80 for 2 pax (included GST and service charges) which I think it is quite reasonable and value for money.I definitely will visit Swatow Seafoods again when craving for Dim Sum even though it is far from my living place.

It is a place for malaysian to ease their heart when they miss home. I always here for its hokien prawn noodle or hokien mee for penang langüòÑ No joke this hokien mee bested some stalls in penang. It used to serve with bak kut but maybe today im abit late, bak kut just gone...

As always, their Prawn and Ikan Belis Satti Soru did not disappoint! Full of flavour and a generous portion too. The Nandu Rasam was also spicy and delicious! No complaints. The service was prompt too! Great treat on May Day üòÅ
Came on a Sunday, preparation of food was really slow (due to the crowd) remember to make a booking before coming for air conditioned table. Overall food quality was mediocre.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: A decent places for cin chat during lunch time! Not crowded
Great location and nice atmosphere. I was just invited to Chinese new year dinner by my friend. It's my first time to taste traditional Chinese new year's cuisine.

Food is above average. beverages could be improved as the drinks we ordered were all too "light" in taste. Milk tea came out really looking like milk, very mild taste of tea. Calamansi ...same issue...mild taste of calamansi.
Fries both the original and sweet potato is good, home style as all the small bits and pieces are served to you, no waste!
For their food prices, just about right as they operate as a standalone cafe

My favourite Boon Tong Kee branch. The service is good; steamed chicken is excellent as always; 3 eggs spinach is great; char siew is so-so. The only dissatisfaction is the rice - not as fragant as its Boon Keng branch in my opinion. Overall, still a good place for steamed chicken rice.
While this is a Known concept for sushi chain. Compared to other sushi chains, the speed of getting our sushi is so so so slow. We waited 30mins and only 3 out of 12 plates ordered came.
Food is good & price is reasonable

Big n succulent pumpkin prawns! Pumpkin sauce is so flavourful you will want to ask for more. Best ribs I've had! Marinated in Ribena for 4hrs and then fried and coated w a mysteriously tasty sauce. The oomph will haunt you until you get your next fix. Do remember to make a reservation or you may have to expect to be turned away. Don't wait! Make your reservation now!

Extremely slow service.  Who would want to wait for 45 mins to collect their order?  It‚Äôs not that they were  super busy. The ladies there, work like it‚Äôs there own home, slow motion.  No urgency, so disturbing to see people work like that in a shop.

Having dinner at Malaysia Boleh, it is not the first time we have the fried kway teow, it comes with a little spicy taste, and that wok hei (wok thermal radiation) is really great! I have seen some stalls that they have the wok hei, but there is some portion of the food got burn. This stall did a good job on that, I dont see any burn on my food. It comes with bean sprout, spring onion green leaves, eggs and 2 median size  prawns! I prefer this spring onion to choy sum, as some times the choy sum might have a bitter taste, love it and will definitely come back again! ‚ù§Ô∏è
Waiting time is roughly about 15 minutes during 7pm on Saturday

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: bought a spicy chicken salad from the toa payoh sushi take out. turns out, after almost finishing the salad, found a bloody worm at the corner. almost wanted to vomit out my food. terrible, will never buy from them again

Surprisingly better than those found in the Chinatown.
Authentic Shanghainese food.
Waited for about 30 mins. Taste not bad.

Was greeted with a nice smell when I entered the restaurant, that reminded me of Banana Leaf Restaurant at Race Course road. Ordered vegetarian satti soru - cooked with tahu sambal and sambar. Portion size was big - can feed two people. Taste wise, I would have liked it spicy though. Tasted somewhat like sambar rice - good for a one-time experience. Will definitely try other vegetarian items the next time. Friendly staff! Highly recommended.

Overwhelmed by the wide selections and price tag at first sight. But take note that it's a masterpiece from an ex-hotel chef. I went on and ordered their Rib Eye Steak with Garlic Merlot Butter Sauce at medium well doneness. Should have gone for medium rare when I saw my friend's cos I'm afraid of my piece of steak keep bleeding ü§£ Anyway, plus point for curly fries!! üôå

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: The serving size is just nice and the pricing is reasonable. Taste is fantastic with good hygiene observed too. One of my go to place for Thai food from now onwards. üëçüèª

Food was decent and there was a promotion for the tomahawk steak which was super delicious. The meat melts in your mouth when savouring.

The seafood plater was a good sharing plate as well making our meal of 4 a happy and enjoyable one.
Fast friendly service. Standard McDonald's menu.
Good quality for food. Can be a bit pricey but definitely value for money.
Ordered black pepper chicken and vegetable. Taste was mediocre and a lil too pricey.

Super friendly staff who goes beyond to make us feel welcome despite us reaching at 9pm+ for a late dinner. Special mention to the very cute auntie who came over and gave us more cucumbers and making sure we have enough rice! Will come back more often! Food is excellent as usual :)
nice
Quality food, nice and tasty. Will come back for more! Prefer the Premium Buta Don to Buta Don as the meat is more tender. Sashimi is fresh but typical.
Quite cosy place to chill out for food. The flavours of food is really delicious. Reaasonable priced with huge portion. Great family hangout place.

The quality of the food is getting from bad to worse. And the service crew at Blk 422 AMK is so rude. I was having my usual lunch alone after a morning run nearby and ordered from them. When the food come, instead of placing the plate of rice in front of me, she placed it one seat away, and the sauce spilled out due to the impact when she placed the food on the table. Did I owe them any money? Or have I been particularly rude to them? I dont think so. So why do the customer warrant such attitude from the service crew? If this is the quality of service you are providing, all the best to your business.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Best Sweet and Sour Beef (Tangsuyook) I had in Singapore! Love the sauce! Strongly recommend with Jjajangmyun! Great food. Fast service and cozy atmosphere. Recommended by a friend who said that this is one of the best Korean Chinese restaurants in Singapore.
First time trying here. Good food. Love the burrito bowl and soft tacos.

Reasonable price Muslim food eg mee siam, lotong, nasi lemak, etc. Fast moving queue as about 5 serving staff work efficiently as each staff serves each customer regardless one or five orders. Seri Muslim Food is located inside 399 Foodcourt.
NTU student favourite food but also the most hated outlet because none of mcdonald deals are applicable to NTU outlet. -.-

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
Nice food and nice place very cosy and relax place
Recommend üëçüòâ
Good vegetarian food. Good service.

Visited this stall at AMK and gave their Tonkotsu Special Ramen a try. I really liked the soup, which was rich and thick, with a meaty milky flavour. Noodles were good, springy and had a nice chew to them. Their Chashu were neatly sliced and tender, which had a mild smoky flavour as well. The eggs were delicate with a silky texture. Overall, it was a competent bowl of ramen with a great value.

Place is a bit of a mini disaster when it comes to service. It does have enough staff who seems genuinely nice, but they all run around like headless chickens. Orders take forever to come after multiple checks with staff, and the place wasn‚Äôt even too packed. Food is nondescript and portion sizes are pathetic.
Xiao long bao was nice and juicy. Spinach was also good. I also ordered Mala noodles. Tried it for the first time and it was good.
Cheap and good Japanese food
Food is not terrible. But, order for only 9 items, took 1.5hour before all dishes are served. Be careful if you want to eat here in saturday after 8pm
i love butter chicken and naan üòÄ
Ordered curry chicken bryani for takeaway.  The curry chicken was tough and bland. Not sure if they had used frozen chicken meat. Will think twice before buying again.

Xiao la is too spicy for me!!!! If i ever go back, i'll totally request for extra extra xiao la, and if it's not possible maybe i'll try their soup version hahaha. But IMHO best best mala xiang guo i've ever tasted!!!! Compulsory topping: EGGS (best cos they scrambled it OMG BEST) and whole fish. I wish it's not too far away from the city cos it takes 1.5 hours to reach NTU sia

My family loves this place, we come here around 5-6 times a year especially on cold nights. The teochew soup is so good and they're quite generous in terms of their portions. I recommend the batang soup and the fried pork belly. super!

The Nasi Goreng Ayam merah the fried chicken is not merah means red in color. It overcooked the chicken become dark color. Luckily the fried chicken the meat is juicy well cook inside. But the fried chicken skin is overcooked raw. I can still satisfy the chicken because the important is the meat is juicy
One if the best place to hang out after midnight. Relaxing and cosy even if the stall is a bit in small in area but very very nice place to relax.
Good ambiance and We enjoyed all the dishes we ordered. We ordered a couple of yakitori, truffle chawanmushi, mentai fries and Gyoza, all taste good. We will be back for more.
Really good Thai food by Thai people with good service. Only problem is expect to wait cause very long queues!
Nice food üëçüèª The service is good. Small cozy traditional cafe located within an industrial building.

Tried the Beef Brisket with aglio olio.
Beef Brisket was soft and tender with good grilled flavour.

downside was that it is quite oily which doused the spaghetti as well, the amount of fat to meat content is pretty high but hard to complain as it‚Äôs brisket and further, at this price point.

(Pardon me for the photo of the half eaten brisket, it was difficult to resist tucking in immediately)
Order via app! Food was served in a timely order. Overall experience with minimal contact with staff except payment. Should improve the app to complete the whole dining experience.

Steamboat is definitely good, broth is flavourful and tasty but can get too salty towards the end..Oyster omelette is also strongly recommended but the rest of dishes such as dim sum, sweet & sour pork, fried tofu, the mixed platter wouldn't be missed. Braised items are also below average.

In conclusion, there are only 2 star items on the items.

Service is slow and expect nothing more. Dishes are also not served in sequence.

If you are not going for steamboat, then don't bother.

Nice Nasi Padang. $5 for 3 sides and a generous portion. Mee siam is not bad $3. Nasi Lemak is not bad too at $3. Usually crowded and full during lunch time. The chicken rice stall is no longer there as of 29 December 2016.

Chicken Cutlet which you can't taste anywhere else in SG.
The magic is in the skin.
It has an alluring, smokey crunch in the skin, and will leave you wanting more.
Have it with their butter rice, and you'll find a match in heaven.

Residents who lives or lived in Clementi or Sunset Way will recognize the stall owner right away.
With his waxy and slick hair combed all the way back, you will also be struck by nostalgia as the aroma and taste of that familiar cutlet bring you back memories of the past.

The Chicken Chop is excellent too!
That is if you can decide which one you want to fill your tummy with.

Economic version of üç£, just like our economic rice. Don't expect quality, but wide range in menu, great for quick fix and chill out. Could get crowded during peak hours as the seats are pretty limited and confined.
The nasi lemak was soft and the fried chicken was so sedap...not forgetting the sambal...it was not too spicy as my kids could eat it...highly recommended if you're looking for gd old malay food...
Plenty of items served in suitable small quantity.  Dishes are good and comparable to other reputable restaurants.  Price for the CNY buffet lunch is reasonable.  Service is good too.
Great Food and Drinks!

Finally found a authentic Korean restaurant that doesn't sell BBQ food ü§£
Wanted to taste an original black bean sauce noodles, and this is just great. The other spicy seafood and Oyster noodles are nice and tasty too. Noodles more like Chinese noodles than the usual Korean Ramen though.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Service was good, staff explained on the menu in details.

Give 4 star for service...
Not the food..
Their service crew are older folks.. so they tend to be more attentive to kids and old folks......
You go in... With kids..
They will get the baby chairs first....
And once awhile will come ask if anything u need.

But the food is plain so so....

The 1 for 1...
From 2.30 pm to 5pm.. is enticing..

But twice we went....
The beef seems very soft and both times my wife says that the beef has a smell..
I tried... It is like... The meat has been defrosted.. in And out of the chiller too many times.....
Not sure. . Maybe some experts can give their views...

Their coke... And coke light ...
Coke light is by the Can.. so they sell $4.
But the coke is $3. Pour by the bottle....
So be prepared the drink doesn't have gas...

As a chain western outlet...
Just plain...
Normal western.

Nice food yet not too expensive and quite affordable depending on people's views. Restaurant has nice interior and seemingly unique exterior. Service is good with friendly waitress who seems to like to talk to customers.

Visited Jubilee Garden several times with the family.

Food's consistently good (not mind-blowingly good, at least at that price point, but you should have a comfortable and enjoyable time). The premium items are are only one serving per table (understandably so but still a bit of a bummer, especially with the chilli crab. The 4 of us had to ration and felt wanting a bit more).

I must add though that service was fantastic - all the service staff were polite and attentive without being intrusive -  kudos to the experienced and well trained staff!
I always go for their Yun nan mi xian (glass noodle soup in a giant bowl). I‚Äôve also tried their minced pork rice set. Tasty meal, very reasonably priced.
Awesome service crew. Was busy working on my laptop. A waitress came by and reminded me to drink my soup first before it turns cold. Like a mum. Thumbs up

Nice handmade fishball! Came too late and all the other ingredients were sold out. Noodles tossed in dark sauce, fried shallots and pork lard which is very fragrant. Wish the pork lard were more crispy.

The place is small but the food is excellent. If you have patience this is the best place to have best Indian food in Singapore.
Must Try : Mutton dish / Biryani / Dosa ( I had chicken stuffed)/ Tea / Prata
The staff is friendly and quick response to our order. The price is reasonable. There will be queue early morning for breakfast.

Quite recommendable place for lunch or dinner. Overall food is good but there,s improvement to be made on the food taste. Especially for the pork rib eye abit too salty. Anyway great job on food presentation. Will come back again to see any improvement on the taste üòÑüòÑ
I ordered plain prata, not oily, crispy and Dahl sauce was fantastic as it was not too spicy also there was a nice fish taste.

Cozy place, less crowded during dinner.

Lots of choices on the menu.
Love the Grilled Beef and Beef noodle soup
Hearty meal.

Service was okay, that‚Äôs the saving grace.

We went on a Saturday night, and there‚Äôs not more than 10 tables of diners inside.

Ordered the Peking Set, and seriously disappointed.

The Peking ducks were so-so.
Chilli crab didn‚Äôt taste like
chilli crab, tasted like tomato sauce crab.
Steamed live grouper, was just okay. Fish was half the size of the plate though.
The Ee-Fu noodles‚Ä¶. Tasted like Char Kway Tiao‚Ä¶. Tasted like noodles stir fried with sweet sauce‚Ä¶
I only ordered teh tarik and it was very bad. Everything went wrong‚Ä¶ it tasted like it was done with Lipton tea bag with some milk. No tarik was done. Very disappointed.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: A great Korean Chinese restaurant that serves my favorite Jjampong and sweet and sour pork. I definately will be back to try this great Chinese food.

Tried the mint chicken, onion omelette, curry chap chye and the $2.50 set which came with a hot drink and roti prata.

The mint chicken curry was full-bodied and the meat was tender; I would recommend you try this if you are looking for something non-spicy. The onion omelette was a generous portion and tasted like how you would expect an onion omelette to taste. On the other hand, the curry chap chye was a let down, being too watery and just not lemak enough.

The roti prata was crispy but tasted like it could have come from a frozen pack, it was served with curry which was pretty good. For $2.50 with a hot drink, I might return and have it again as a breakfast or afternoon snack.
Not much to say about it except it is just super tasty. Love their soft taco with grilled chicken or steak!
Good service and many tables to sit and have the meal.
Consistently good through the years! The prawn paste chicken stood out the most for me. It was well seasoned with a light and crispy batter.

A casual dining restaurant with reasonable pricing. The steak is good and comes with seasonal promotion most of the time. One may top up to a set to make it a complete meal. And there‚Äôs a wide range of different types of coffee that you can upgrade, which I personally love the mocha.

The lunch set meal comes with a soup with a garlic bread, a main, a dessert and a cup of coffee/tea, which can all be upgraded at a small cost. Lately there‚Äôs also a one for one promotion during weekdays lunch.

With the membership sign up, you may redeemed points which is converted to cash rewards, plus other benefits, such as birthday e-voucher.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Had a wide variety of satisfying dim sum at this place.  I have to say that generally it was quite enjoyable though the standards were uneven.  For example, while the Chee cheong fun and the char siew pau, char siew seu and har kau were well done, the potstickers were done with too thick a skin and the egg custard buns didn't exactly ooze with goodness.  Nonetheless you get what you paid for and you would have an okay experienxd if you choose the right dishes.

Had a nice evening out with frens at this new kid on the block- Semma bar. Nice ambience, cosy, great for dinner or just hanging out with frens. The food was exceptionally good, especially the very tender mysore mutton which came on a hotplate. We also tried the prawns, roti john, mutton satti soru, some sharing platter and a fried ikan bilis with onion dish which went very well with drinks. They also had some interesting drinks like Thalapathy and Nayagan! Was full house by 8pm... in short, a nice hangout with great food!
Lucky our queue wasn't too long. Had a great brunch and variety of dim sum to choose.
Really really good pasta, even better service ‚ù§Ô∏è
Quality of food letter bit down need to maintain.
really nice ambience and quick service, plus the food was honestly pretty good! i really liked the peach lemonade too~
Gud Indian option inside NTU
The only Japanese stall at this Hawker Centre.

(Translated by Google) Claypot Chikin is good. The seasoning goes well with the rice, and the rice is recommended. Most of the menu is Chinese food, so you can order with confidence. Stir-fried bean sprouts are also delicious with a gentle taste.
