Set meals are super value for money, quality food and portion is generous with  different varieties.Been ordering from grabfood but I think dine in quality is so much better.. only issue is there are lots of managers and servers but everyone is so u friendly and unattentive.

Had the spring chicken and chicken cutlet with rice. Price quite reasonable though on the tad high which can be understood due to business expenses
Will visit again.
Food was excellent!! Really enjoyed my lunch

The food portion is huge for main course and good for sharing. Taste was ok but nothing wow us. It was full house when we visited and the service was a little underwhelming. The restaurant is obviously short of hands. The staffs are very strict to covid measures, which is certainly good for us. Overall experience was ok. But visit again? Maybe no.

Portion is very small for large.  Was charged $40 for 2 portions of large noodles and $20 for 2 miserable pieces of toufu with a few minced pork at the top. Total $60.  Really a ripped off coz the large portion is like medium.

Update: Ate at another zichar store today and spent $86 for 5 medium dishes and rice. Medium portion was like zhenwei's large. There was even leftover coz we were so full after the meal. Really value for money unlike this zhenwei. Will not patronise Zhenwei again.
Very popular. Can wait 30min on weekend evening.

North Indian Cuisine at its finest

This is truly a hidden gem and we were surprised to find it on our way to The Science Centre. We decided to have both Lunch and dinner at Phoenix as the Food & Service is really remarkable!

For lunch the Vegetarian Biryani and Chicken Biryanis were superb!
For dinner we had 4 types of Naan Bread, Chana Masala, Palak Paneer and Fish Masala. The food is amazing!

I am really fascinated by their speed in service and above all the food is simply affordable. Do look out for Mr. Jovan Tan, the fine gentleman who took good care of us when we dined at Phoenix.

Our empty plates, speak for itself. Special compliments to the Chef's!

Good value, tasty and surprisingly big portions. We over ordered as we thought the rice bowls were normal sized but they were huge.

The salmon fish head was huge.

The potato salad is good but relatively expensive at $5.80 before service charge.

Food is ordered via scanning a QR code.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: This place has a great food with Low price ! The place is rather hot. We love the san lau mee, the shrimp paste chicken is so so this time round. The sotong kang kong is salty. Good for gathering. Seats are limited so go earlier if you can. Gather a few friends and go and share dishes. This time round we didn‚Äôt order prawn roll which I love!
Good food good service at reasonable prices. Set meals are a good deal with good spread of nice food.
It‚Äôs the best prawn noodles I had in Singapore. Totally must try!!
1st time trying this place, recommended by friends. Few good dishes that I like, including the prawns omelette, which is not that oily. Prawn cake is nice too. On the whole, recommended with 4-stars.

Great food, great service.

If I could eat the Hamachi Carpaccio every day I would. Perfectly seasoned and a burst of joy with each mouthful.

Highly recommend the beef bowl and wagyu sliders. The chicken karaage was ok but probably only seemed average in contrast with the outstanding taste of the other dishes we had.

Got there 3 minutes before the happy hour wagyu slider promotion ended and our server was very kind to quickly lock it in for us. Very good value of a delicious slider with our sake ordered. Will be back!
Good food at a good price in smaller portions so you won't over-eat.

Been eating here everyday. Their steak with garlic butter is so good!
The chef is the friendliest man too. My paylah messed up so I double paid. Only realised 4 days later. When I explained the problem, he refunded cash to me with a smile :)
GrabFood estimate isn't accurate. Took 30mins for order to be ready, not 10mins.
Best mala restaurant in NTU, and some say jurong. Must try the mala tang

If u want to enjoy something very Korean Chinese food, you must try here.  Every time I visited here, all the menu I tried made always me feel I was at home, Korea.  Still keep exploring other different dishes, nothing let me down so far.

Adding on Sep 19th, 2020
This restaurant seems to have become more popular these days.  The hall is full of local young generations at 11:40am and even such a long queue outside.  Hope this one keeps the same quality forever.

The ingredients of the medium pack is the SAME as the small pack, the difference is mainly the amount of RICE!

Ordered takeaway at 6:25 pm and was told to collect the food 45 mins later. When I got back, the food wasn‚Äôt ready yet. Gave them the benefit of doubt, came back to check another 25 mins later, where‚Äôs my food?! Oh, after the second time they finally ‚Äòchecked‚Äô the order and my takeaway was ready in 3 mins.

Not worth the wait or queue in my opinion, in terms of service, food portion and quality. Perhaps the north side just lacks a really good authentic claypot rice!
Decent western food and at an affortable price.
I really like the Aglio Oglio here, will continue to try other food.

We have lunch yesterday at this restaurant. We are happy with the variety of dishes available. The food portion is generous and the food tasted delicious. The service staff are friendly and served with a smile.

The services and the food quality exceeded our expectations and we will definitely return for lunch and dinner.

2nd visit, this time remember to take picture before I stir. Lol.
Ordered their specialty again @10.80 which is good priced since it is in a coffeeshop (no point to pay high price at shopping malls just because of their high rental)
Different people has different preferences for ramen so I'll just share what I like about this.
Thumbs up for the texture of the noodles and the thick, favourable broth (those who love thick broth shld try)

Ramen lovers Should at least give it a try to see if you love it.
Good and authentic Malay dishes. The sambal goreng is really nice.

Heard some blogger recommended this claypot rice.
Personally nothing special about the food. Order a medium size claypot rice. Ingredients quite generous but taste too plain. Nothing special or distinctive that make me wow at all. Not salty not sweet. Not fragrance. Rice too soft and broken once we mixed it.
Ordered a side dish Hakka Crispy pork. Indeed crispy and tender meat but tasteless‚Ä¶ not salty nor sweet. Can‚Äôt taste any special at all with the ‚Äúred‚Äù crispy flour coating.
Consider ‚Äúheathy‚Äù Low salt Low sugar?‚Äù

Ordered quite a few dishes to share but the only memorable dish for me was their signature claypot chicken. The staff also took the wrong order for our soup.

The mapo tofu was shocking as the tofu pieces were so big and it wasn't spicy at all. The eggplants were also a disappointment as they were not diced and it was tough in the middle and not flavoured enough.
Tried their Mee rebus and lontong. Both really good. To be honest I felt it was better than all the other stalls opened in the morning in this coffeeshop.

First off, we were given the wrong order even after repeated confirmations. We were given one egg prata less but as it was a take away, we could not rectify the error.

The prata was one of the least nice prata our family has eaten. It was very oily and "doughy".
The dhal curry was a huge disappointment.

Will not recommend this place unless you have a prata craving that desperately needs to be satisfied.

The best putien outlet in Singapore. Food is delicious, service is fantastic, servings are generous. Very attentive staff. There are a lot of food options at Northpoint but we have been coming here almost every other week for the past 3 years. My daughter loves the friendly staff and food.

Food is yummy and sashimi is fresh ,nice view ,indoor feel so cooling . If you wish to have more privacy ,can choose to seat at outdoor ,it's a nice area . Staffs is polite . Well will visit the place again.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: One of the many Crystal Jade outlets serving traditional Chinese cuisine from the different provinces of China. Food quality is decent and certainly good valued. Won't blow a hole in the wallet. Service is quite efficient even during peak hours. 3.5 stars
Excellent  menu and healthful preparation  of food. Awesome pumpkin soup!

I dont usually write google reviews for food places unless it‚Äôs exceptionally good but THIS RESTAURANT‚Ä¶

Decided to visit this restaurant after reading all the good reviews on google but it turned out to an utter disappointment.

Was greeted with a weird mouldy stench when we stepped into the shop and the interior is a bit run down. Staff were not friendly and made us feel that they don‚Äôt wanna work anymore lol.

All the rice bowls on the menu looked so generous so we were very excited, however upon the arrival of our food, we were shocked and disappointed. $26 for a palm size rice bowl? Ps, I have small palm so imagine how small it is.

Trying to stay positive, we told ourselves maybe the food quality really superb. After taking a few bites on their sashimi, we looked at each other with disappointment. Not only it‚Äôs not fresh, had a few with fish scale and bones in it. We then moved on to eating the rice thinking it wouldn‚Äôt go wrong. I mean, ITS PLAIN SUSHI RICE. To our dismay, the rice doesn‚Äôt even taste like sushi rice??? There‚Äôs no vinegar taste AT ALL. It‚Äôs VERY STICKY, I think it‚Äôs glutinous rice???

Miso soup tastes worse than the ones I get from donki and the soya sauce is so salty it doesn‚Äôt even taste like the usual sashimi soya sauce they serve in restaurants???

In the end, although the dishes weren‚Äôt cheap, we really cannot bring ourselves to finish the food. ITS THAT HORRIBLE. I love my chirashi dons and I‚Äôve never not been able to finish them but this restaurant really outdid themselves.

If you are looking for quality Japanese food, this restaurant ain‚Äôt it.
Food was good, service was quick and responsive. Friendly and helpful staff.
absolutely worst ‚Äúkimchi‚Äù fried rice, absolutely tasteless and even mushy.  pure rubbish, should have checked out the reviews before buying food from here.
love sushi! u should only come before peak hours as the food comes very fast and u dont rlly have to wait when u are hungry‚Ä¶ avoid peak hours!!!

Best satay ever. No short cut with fats trimming between meat like those in other satay places.

New Rebus and Soto, still the best.. Wow so yummy.

Lok lok varieties and selections not much and prices a bit on the high side for ala cart menu.. For those who loves lok lok and big eater.. buffet is more suitable..
Ambience wise normal.. location not bad with other good eateries around..
Awesome place to enjoy a family Chinese dinner with strong flavours and all dishes are tasty. Worthy
Service was great, by the team.
Great dinner here..  service very good. Would come again soon.

Passed by & the smell of Pork Sisig caught our noses. Ordered 1 to try and loved it!
The lady staff was really friendly & polite too!

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
Forgot to take picture of food but I'm posting the photo instead.

Three things I would like to talk about

1. Food and price

The food they served was fresh and delicious, especially their corn and marinated beef! Their bomb is the signature sauce, superb! I'll rank it my top three favourite sauce. My friends and I were praising the signature sauce profusely! Another innovation of them is to use butter to grill the meat, it was super delicious! Total price we paid after 10% discount was $52 for 4 pax. That's super worthy and even without 10%, it's still under $15 with your stomach full!

2. Cleanliness

Normally mookata place will be very dirty and unhygienic and oily, but they're otherwise, the whole environment is clean and not oily at all, table don't have any dirt or leftover food. Which we all were very pleased with.

3. Staff

Staff was super friendly and attentive, despite they have to attend to other customers, they will drop by to ask how's the food and if there's any assistance needed, and also offered to take picture for us. I will rate the service 10 stars if Google allows.

Even though the location can be very ulu, but it's really worth your time to walk in and try their food.
Awesome & Delicious food

No frills Japanese dons and grilled sticks at reasonable prices. Serving can take some time. The dons were tasty and well seasoned, but it feels a bit like Chinese cooking on Japanese ingredients. Mushrooms were well grilled, gyoza was not as crispy as expected, mackarel fish rice was a reliable bowl.
Pleasant air-conditioned environment for dining. Food is palatable and lunch deals come with a free drink.
Expensive and taste so so only

Food here is better than the average Chinese restaurant, and there were certain dishes that stood out. One of them was definitely the hor fun which had a good wok hei and the sweetness from the vegetables really complemented the dish well. The duck was also really tender and the skin was crisp. I think the volcano chicken was average and the KL
Hokkien mee is definitely a miss from me. I sat indoors and the restaurant got a little stuffy as the lunch crowd came. Overall it‚Äôs a decent place to have a meal, but there‚Äôs limited parking available and reservations are recommended if indoor seating is preferred.
Fried kway teo is not Penang style more local style, fried with sweet sauce and Chinese sausage. Chendol not using fresh coconut milk. Disappointing :(
Went there as recommended by a friend, chicken and beef are very well marinated, soup was good and scallops were huge. Yum!!!!

The crispy rice bits and chilli are always highlights of the claypot rice. Garlic fried chicken & hakka fried pork are some of my go to dishes whenever I'm here. First time trying the Thai style Yong tau foo and greatly enjoyed the Thai chilli sauce that came with it - refreshing pineapple notes! Bittergourd egg and San lou mifen were also lovely.

Great for small or big groups - you can always call in advance to pre-order.

Finally got to try this place along jalan kayu, which happened to be open despite being CNY D3! We walked past a couple of times and it‚Äôs always filled with long queues. Food is pretty tasty, decent pricing although the portions tend to be slightly on the small side! Must haves: salted egg chicken, ngoh hiang, furong egg (has lots of ingredients inside and very soft!)! Toilet is super clean, like that at orchard road!
Very nice thai food. Tomyum soup was abit too spicy. But v nicr overall. Better than Nakhon Kitchen imo. Overheard their Dry Kway Chup is a must try!
Good service

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Do not order their Nasi Goreng Ikan Bills from Food Panda my first time buying give bad impression from AMK branch, look at the rice use curry and cook so little vegetables and almost blank, rice is so dry no much ingredients $5 expensive will never üëé order again! I stick to my Bishan Srisun Prata üíØ better than your Al Mubin nonsense popular!

Opening hours is similar to restaurant timing as there is a break from 2.30pm to 5pm.

Pork tomahawk is only limited to 10 servings per day and they open from 11.15am. So if you go after lunch hours... hoping they can increase the par level.

Ordered chicken & pork chop. Pretty much like Collins but it's way much cheaper. Black pepper sauce is spicy and so is the alio olio. So do remind the counter staff if you are ordering for the kids. Overall its very nice and tasty. Meat is not dry and rather juicy. Serving is generous and value for money.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Serves food fast despite having quite a number of customers in the shop. Staff is also very helpful. The plain prata is crispy which is very enjoyable with their fish curry. The egg prata is also crispy which takes away the feeling of the soft center of the egg when biting into the parts.

The teh halia, while having a pleasant strong ginger taste, is a bit too sweet for my taste.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Lousy packages. My char siew and roasted pork rice.. soggy with sauces. Order thru Deliveroo!!!

(Translated by Google) The sesame sauce dry mixed with Mala Tang is delicious. I haven't tried it before, but I don't want to eat the salted soup version. I heard that there will be a branch. It should also have a good place kk

The purple rice in the yogurt can't bite the yogurt. The taste of yogurt is really too cheap. Buying drinks is so unprofessional. It's better to focus on selling hot pot drinks. More and more fans may spend a lot of money to eat what you want to eat. At least 15-20 can't run away. The package seems to be priced in the early ten dollars, but it is only enough to stuff your teeth. If you like fatty beef noodles or something, you can also update the staff. The frequency of replacement is a bit too high. Generally speaking, the price/performance ratio is slightly lower. The taste is not enough. The price is better. The taste is cheaper.

New spot for springleaf prata with Safra since May 2021, this location by the pool side... nearly. located outside / beside swimming pool entrance. Fast service with plenty of space both in air con or open environment. Prata and Briyani are easy choices, nice cozy environment at almost FC price.

Cycled there for breakfast. Tried the paper thosai & it is awesome! Crispy on the outside & soft inside. Butter is added on the batter when cooking. Only SGD$2. The fish curry has strong fish smell. Preferred the vege curry. The chutney is spicy. The owner refilled my curry when I asked for it. Worth it!

Food stalls with many varieties of dishes such as Chillu Ban Mian (Dry/Soup), Penang Carrot Cake & Kwey Tiew, Nasi Lemak, Rujak & Popiah, Cendol Ice, Claypot Rice, Porridge, Noodles Soup. Just that they do not have Assam Laksa, sadly :(
Seems to be short staffed and as a result, poor attitude and service. First and last time at yuba hut.
A great place to get some dim sum and Cantonese food. Love the Jumbo prawn wanton noodle as well. Can be quite crowded and noisy.

Worst food portions ever, when confronted they tell you that the food is being weighted to be fair. We paid $8 for a $2 portion. Sure we understand the high rentals etc but charging $8 for subpar food and horrendous food portions not even fit for a cat is just too much.

The attitude of the hawkers are horrendous as well.

Malaysian food is cheap to begin with, cut with the pretense. Not recommended unless you are too rich and want your mood to be spoiled.

Food was excellent and service was great too. Staff very friendly and accommodating. They also took steps to ensure safe distancing. Parking is little hard but they offer free valet which is a huge plus. Will definitely be back!
They have thick pork chops on without a thick price tag.

The potion is very big even for mini bowl. The food is managed like work of art and I can feel the chef must be enjoyed in making the dishes. The sashimi is fresh and indeed a lot !!! A little Jem in my neighborhood and hope it can get more n more popular

Best penang prawn soup in Singapore. Better than 888 in penang, more heavy taste here. Now they have the dry one available, but I always come for the soup one. And they have big prawns too, I had it 10 years ago for $3.50/$4.

Uncle friendly and straightforward guy, but most importantly his hands are fast. No need to queue so long. Try it when you are around. :)
#ERROR!

You will find traditional #DimSum here at #SwaTowSeafoodRestaurant (aka #Ê±ïÂ§¥Êµ∑È≤ú). Taste is decent and nostalgic. Been here for many years, however due to covid, last visit was about 2 years+ ago.
.
#StanzFoodHunts @swatowrestaurant #ChineseCuisine  #ChineseBreakfast #ToaPayoh

Fluffy and fragrant rice. Ikan bilis and chicken wings are crispy and tasty. The best is still the chilli sambal, which makes the nasi lemak complete. Too bad the whole lot of otah were snapped up through a pre-order and didn't get to taste the complete royal rumble. Next time.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Overall food is below average. I'm not sure is it due to busy Saturday dinner crowds or what, the standard is not what was expected. Yusheng is tasteless. The fire chicken has special presentation but tastewise is just average. Even common dish like cereal prawn is disappointing -- prawns are chewy, texture more like sotong than prawns.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Ordered 1 naan set and waited forever ...  The front is very disorganized and everything is just slow... Food is not bad though

Slow service although the place is not crowded stepped in almost 4pm. Tried very hard to signal the waitresses but to no avail. Got to walk up to them to inform that we wanted to order. Food wise is as usual. Still as good
Gyu don at $9, buta don at $8. Grilled squid at $7. Price and taste are okay. Portions commensurate with price. You'll still be hungry after a don if you're an adult male.

the rice is in green colour and the taste is good. I didnt try the chicken wing but it shall be ok to try. we went on tuesday lunch time and there's less people. the sauce is not in red but abit orange colour, so it's less spicy but abit sweet for me. they also sell curry puff.
One of the best south Indian Briyani i have had in Singapore. Happy hour beer added. Cool place to chill with beer and chicken tikka

Will give 0 star if its possible.. see the review 5 stars so when ahead to try their ala carte buffet, but then to my horror, food taste horrible, food is all reheat, it was so hard to eat as in literally solid hard food that it is inconvenient for my parent (which is elderly) to eat.

Order their duck meat and worst, is was still raw,which then i told their manager, female waitress which wore a blazer. She just reply "Oh we cut out from the peking duck." and walk away, but so what? it is still raw!!!!  It was so bad that even if free i wouldnt go back.

If you are considering to bring your family or friend over, can just forget it. there are plenty more buffets or resturant are cheaper and taste way better then their. Dont get bluffed by the 5 stars review. who knows if it their own people

No photo provided as i wouldnt want to review but the more i think, i feel that this have to be reviewed
Prata is nice. Masala dosai also nice. They serve other food too.
I ate here after my game today. Food and service were great! They even accept PayNow!

friendly stall owner, gives great vibes! ordered the fried fish with mashed potato and onion rings as sides. also ordered an ala carte side of chicken nuggets. portion was quite generous, really worth the $13 i paid for the meal :) thanks for the meal!!

We had the Egg Prata, Egg+Cheese Prata, Plain Prata, and Paper Prata with Sugar. We liked all, except the egg+cheese prata which was slightly salty! The pratas in general were crispy which was great. We preferred the fish curry to the chicken curry, although it was slightly spicier, which some might not appreciate. Affordable prices as always!

A worthwhile visit. Nice and sumptuous food is served at Din Tai Fung. I enjoy the beef noodles which has a super stock base for their soup, taste like essence of beef. The pork dumplings are my favourite as well. Enjoy.

The food is absolutely delicious and served by friendly staffs too! Will definitely come again! üòäüëçüèª

The picture below is named Half Curry Udon for $6.90, and I loved it!  üòä
Cannot request to sit somewhere else even though having many empty table around. (Still not ordering)The waitress very rude and strictly cannot sit on other table. Very bad service.

Traditional Claypot Rice, Sambal Sotong, Qing Long Cai Ê∏ÖÈæôËèú. While they do have a traditional style claypot rice, I didn't feel like this place is worth making a trip down for when I have better options at Holland Drive.  The sambal sotong was not what I expected and was a meh.
Pretty good!!!! Their mala has KICK

Not sure if they will be increasing their price, but the quality of the food has not dropped since lots of things happening since 2022, Noticed that they changed their stall location, and that the newer generation has taken over the stall, the Chicken wings are the best to pair with their fragrant rice, and their sambal is top notch as well.

Will definitely visit again.

Not open in the morning. But they seems like selling more and promoting beer. Perhaps a heaven for beer drinker in this neighbourhood. There are many trace of Japanese decor, with huge lanterns and many seemingly art object that represent Japanese culture spew around the premise. The garden is well kept to look so natural and I love the entrance to the small tavern. Yes tavern. Hidden away in the garden on a small mold. The rising step tells me that I am ascending to some higher plane. Drinking. LOL

We came here again yesterday. Love the food and the environment. Will come more often.
Improve please
It is always a good place to eat alone or with your friends and families. Dim Sum here is tasty and juicy~ A very good choice for Cantonese food lovers~
Delicious and fast service even sometimes very crowded
Reasonable price western food and comfortable environment. Will go back there again.

Went there for lunch recently for a family of 5. Overall food is nice and the service is good. However, and that is a HUGE but, the waiting time for the food is ridiculously long at 70 minutes after ordering!!

They did let us know that waiting time for food will be at 30 minutes or more. I think it is good that they let customers know that they need to wait. Hmm... but we waited for 70 minutes... AND even if there is lots of pre-warning or notification that food may take some time to prepare, waiting for 70 minutes for the food is not acceptable. They really need to look into streamlining the process or expanding the kitchen capacity to have faster turn around time.

Apart from that, please do make reservation ahead! With such a long turn around time from ordering food to serving, you don't want to be queueing outside waiting for table + waiting for food later!

The service of this place is good. There are many attentive young servers.

Food wise, it is tasty and unique. Some notable dishes are the Spinach Creatm Tagliatelle ($15), Seafood Aglio Olio ($15),  CCB (Cream Corn Bacon $9). We ordered quite a lot of other stuff too. Can look at the photos. Food wise, it is 5 stars.

Enjoyed Good food
Although seats are limited we had to wait for our seats
It's been years since I'd been returning for great food here. Their mee soto, mee rebus, gado2, satays are just superb. You know they're open, when you see a long queue right to their shop üòãüòâ
Great experience. Small Japanese Eatery serving generous amount of meat. Pork belly is juicy and sauce goes well with the rice. Will come back again soon!

Buta Kakuni Don($9.20)
Meat is flavourful and hard but still able to chew. Comes with rice, seaweed, ginger and half a marinated egg.

Unagi Chirashi Don($9.20)
Like the rice coral of the pearl sea blooms with the petal of silky smooth sweet Unagi tango with the pistil spicy tangy pickled radish.
A taste that bless the soul.üòã

Ebiko Eel Roll($9.30)(8 pcs)üòÑ
Traffic Light(Crabmeat, Tamago, Cucumber) sushi holding an umbrella of sliced Unagi while withstanding the heavy downpour of Mentaiko rain and hail of ebiko. What a storm of umaminess it cause to Traffic Light sushi-san.‚õàÔ∏è‚òîüòã

Food is good. Services needs to improve.
The crispy pork is a must try. Shark fins come in huge portion. The others are so so. The service needs to improve. Many aunties working. Never ask before changing the plates, after changing the plate. Even dare to wipe the fingers on our wipes.
One of the best meals i ever had. Every single dish was delicious. Prompt and efficient service. Will definitely return, thank you ! ;)

There for a reunion visit of our secondary school premises. Service was not the most efficient as we were served a satay platter instead of a satay pizza as we had ordered. The ambience was relaxing and food was good. Although it wasn‚Äôt a busy night, staff did not really pay much attention to us. Would still come back again.
My first experience  trying mexican food was at vatos urban tacos & was utterly disgusted by them.  hence was a little decisive on coming here. Glad i came ,the quesadillas & food here are delicious!

Dining experiences @ Tasha‚Äôs have been great so far! One of our frequent go to joints. Service is always good! Friendly and alway ready to take feedback. The aunties always come forward to check if the meals are all good. We had tried the prata, thosai, both chicken and mutton biryani, murtabak, mutton chop and tea. The food is really good and better than what we had at Springleaf. Generally, the food is not too salty or overly sweet. Meats are always soft and well cooked. Curries are rich and flavorful. It does not leave a heavy queasy feeling after the meals. You can ask for a lesser sugar Tehs‚Ä¶ and the tea does not have the astringency of the tea (not ‚Äúsiap‚Äù).

Ordered via Grab Food.
The Heng Hwa Bee Hoon ÂÖ¥ÂåñÁ±≥Á≤â taste alright. The salted egg pumpkin is reasonable though I would preferred lesser flour version.

Wonderful thai food!! Everything is wonderful, especially the lemongrass salad. We ordered: olive fried rice, stuffed chicken wings, Kang kong, fried fish, Tom yum soup, pad gra pow, glass noodles. The balance of sweet, sour, spicy and salty in the dishes were great.

Desserts and drinks also recommended!
Having good breakfast here to start a day

This is the worse outlet with the worst customer service by their staffs!

As if walked in customers will know what is left for us to order when all your sign boards are lit up! Staffs have zero respect to walked in customers as they did not even bother to turn and face customers!

To the staffs, if you are not interested to work, you better quit your job and don't affect the branding Malaysia Chiak!

1 star is Over Rated

This place has the one of the crispiest (but not as crispy as that in the Thomson branch) but their butter chicken is a no-go!! My friends and I ordered that to share last Saturday, and was shocked to get one piece of chicken thigh (pardon the half-eaten chicken but I only thought to snap a photo after digging in). It was barely enough for 2/3 people and i think it is $6.90 (correct me if i'm wrong). You get the idea! too expensive for just a chicken thigh covered in butter chicken sauce.

I ate their butter chicken at their other branch along Thomson area a few weeks ago and that was so much better, with decent portion of butter chicken.

Would recommend to go to their original branch as they have more decent portions and crispier prata.
Very friendly staff with good service!

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Good food and nice environment

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
We are here as it was raining and it felt like a perfect time for thai hotpot hahaha. Reminds me of the good old days at marina south Zhengfa.

Not much to gush about, normal fare. Good crowd for a rainy day ‚ò∫Ô∏è

Went to this place at 520pm, was not crowded at all. However, despite the low crowd levels, the waitress was still very impatient in taking our order. She got irritated when we changed our order and ignore us when we tried to confirm the order one last time and just walked away. So upsetting as we visited the place with high expectations. Poor service! The food is not bad, a 6.5 upon 10.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
To the management of Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle @Blk 308 Anchorvale Road

Please educate your workers. Not well stay at home.
Case No. 63884 and 63886 were not well, yet still continue to go to work. The 27yo Malaysian (63886)  already developed loss of taste but DID NOT SEEK MEDICAL ATTENTION!!!!! Now it's a cluster!!!! Everyone Q-ing for swab test outside the clinic, all the way to the bakery shop, which will affect the business too!!!!

(Translated by Google) A more authentic Chinese restaurant, covering a wide range of cuisines, including dishes from the north and the south. The dishes are delicious, and the pot of pork and scallion pancakes are recommended. Fish-flavored shredded pork with less sugar has no sweetness. If you are not used to it, you can consider some others.

(Original)
ÊØîËæÉÂú∞ÈÅìÁöÑ‰∏≠È§êÂ∫óÔºåË¶ÜÁõñÁöÑËèúÁ≥ªÊØîËæÉÂπøÔºåÂåóÊñπÂçóÊñπÁöÑËèúÈÉΩÊúâÂÅö„ÄÇËèúÈÉΩÂæàÂ•ΩÂêÉÔºåÈîÖÂåÖËÇâ‰ª•ÂèäËë±Ê≤πÈ•ºÊØîËæÉÊé®Ëçê„ÄÇÈ±ºÈ¶ôËÇâ‰∏ùÂä†Á≥ñÂ∞ëÊ≤°‰ªÄ‰πàÁîúÂë≥Ôºå‰∏ç‰π†ÊÉØÁöÑÂèØ‰ª•ËÄÉËôëÁÇπÂÖ∂‰ªñÁöÑ„ÄÇ

Strong contender to the existing upper Thomson road cafes like Columbus Coffee. Overall good brunch food, with nice platting and interior design. However could do better with their coffees (quite awful Americano). They should like consider providing better utensils (fork,soon) as the current ones are obviously of sub standard quality, similar to the ones we see in food court. It‚Äôs the non polished type and didn‚Äôt look or feel sparkling clean. Furthermore, all of their fork has stains between the grooves. Asked for change but all had stains. Ended up not using their fork. Lost my appetite a little. Chicken was great but wished they drained the excess oil before serving. The plate was filled with excess oil from the chicken midway during meal. Overall 3 stars with lots of potential for improvement.

Savory porridge! Tried the pork meatballs with sliced pork - TBH ingredients weren‚Äôt to shout for, but the porridge made it up for it :) think they cook the ingredients in the porridge to let the marinate and sweetness soak through.
Ingredient portions were pretty generous. Price-wise - depending on ingredients, betw $5.50-$10plus.

What you see in this photo is priced at $14++ on their menu. This place is nice and cozy, and the food comes hot. Waitress should have clarified orders because she got one of our orders wrong (Chashu don became Katsu don), and when we informed her about it after it came, she said nothing. I mentioned it again when paying and all she said was that she heard us say Katsu don. Not a single word of apology of sorts. Upon opening (we were there at 11.12am), we were informed that because they had just opened, there was no cold soba available either as the sauce just got put into the fridge. Generally disappointing but thank goodness for Burpple 1-for-1.
Went here twice and good thing that it was not crowded. Environment is cozy and food tastes ok and decently priced. Convenient place for dining after doing some exercise at SAFRA.
$8.30 for a bowl of char siew ranmen. .all OK except I find the photo and manual not so clear. Hope u can improve on the manual part. See until blur.
Was at AMK outlet, no frills ramen at heartland prices. Served by friendly staff Peggy!
DO NOT BUY THEIR BAH KUT TEH. I just had one here, $7 with rice. There isn‚Äôt much meat, mostly bones and mushroom. This should be regarded as a scam for $7. Never coming back again.
Nice food. Great staff

I tried this after noticing many older folks patronising this. Had the Tioman fish +century egg + egg porridge. The porridge base was certainly good, and the onsen egg was a nice touch. The fish slices were thick and fresh, but there was a freshwater fish taste to it. If I did not include the add ons, the amount of ingredients in the porridge would have been a bit little. The you tiao was too hard and a bit too chewy and the oil used to fry it was not very fresh. I would eat the porridge again if I‚Äôm in the vicinity and have a craving, but $11.30 for a porridge meal is pricey.

The food might be good, I would never know because we couldn‚Äôt even pay for the food. Ok sure, they are old fashion, no paylah, no paynow, no contactless payment, in short only cash or nets, even with a paylah sticker there below the countertop ( which is misleading) The staff generated some QR code for my wife to scan but this turned out to be a dead end as my wife‚Äôs money got deducted but payment was declined. While this is common in many restaurants, we are not faulting the restaurant for that but it‚Äôs the attitude of the cashier that suddenly became very rude. First he threw the receipt at us saying ‚Äúlook, payment didn‚Äôt go thru, I also dunno coz it never goes thru‚Äù (then why generate it in the first place) .So my wife asked him for help and what can we do now?, is there any other way, coz the payment went thru on our side. He replied, ‚Äúthen you all just wait, I also dunno what to do, payment didn‚Äôt go thru‚Äù. His tone was quite loud and not acceptable for me. There are multiple ways this situation can be handled but raising tone and being rude to customers is definitely not the way.  So we went away and tried to call the bank while the staff just ignored us and went to serve other. I got seriously annoyed by this lack of professionalism and manners, and once we managed to get the money back, we left. Once again, they might have the best tasting Thai food in the world, but with that kind of attitude, I would not step in that place again. If you want to go, bring cash/nets, then probably the staff will be nice to you.

Might be a blessing in disguise. Went to the toilet, and on the way, you can see how poorly maintained the kitchen is, not to mention filthy. Might have saved us on a case of stomach pain/ diarrhoea. My advice for your management : 1. we are in the freaking 21st century Singapore, not some ulu kampungs , update your methods of payment for more variety. 2. Talk properly to your customers. Who do you think you are to be rude? 3. Clean your kitchen or at least put a curtain to hide all your mess from your customers eyes.
Value for money, superb food even with takeaway.  Ordered again for mums birthday and always good so far.

Really good Indian restaurant, we frequently go there when we visit the science center.
Staff is friend and food really tasty.
The only 2 areas I would suggest to improve would be:
- to add some sound absorbing panel, restaurant is really noisy during peak hours
- improve kids menus with vegetables, as it only propose fried food as main dishes

Old school nasi lemak with a kampung homestyle taste that's so hard to find these days. Took me right back to my childhood.

The nasi was lightly fragrant and fluffy, unlike the overly lemak versions you get at most food centres. The simple standard $1 pack with selar kuning, slice of omelette, cucumber and sambal is very good on its own, but there are other dishes from the nasi padang array if you want add ons.

Now curious about their other breakfast standards like mee rebus, mee siam and the soto. Will be back to try!

Tastes above average hawker western food.. the portion really worth the price paid.. use shopee pay to get even further discount!

Update 08/05: this stall tastes so much better than the one at S-11 food court that used to be quite famous until their standard dropped...

Bad experienced today, staff very rude. Nagging, bad temper, bear brunt and attack customer from counter then Start charging outside the counter and to the dining table. Worst still bad mouthing customer with other patrons such an attitude and unprofessional... only stop when I started to record a video and intended to call police. So childish and easily get offended by small miscommunication over Teh O Kosong and when I took the shop pictures... keep nagging and grumpy like old man.

A man attacking women over small matter? Thats so uncalled for. Consider to report to police, I have the videos. Oh another man also came to our dining table and after I recorded him ... he walked away immediately. You guys gangsters?

Ordered gam hiong prawn fried rice ($8.90), using the advance order. The whole process was very smooth, and I got my order on time, and my fried rice was still piping hot. Generous portion of fried rice, and I counted more than 6 prawns (amaziiinggg), and wok hei was there! üëçüèª

Superb food and service! Food is not too salty nor sweet it‚Äôs really palatable and feels healthy! Service is also good and staff are all very friendly! Would like to commend a staff Wei Li Hui as she provided exceptional friendliness and does check up on customer food and service satisfaction. Overall I recommend people to dine in at Putien Northpoint!
Wonderful Filipinos food. Great service and great selection of wines and liquors.

Tried their set menu for 4 persons. We like the braised pork, tofu, and salted chicken (looks dry but it‚Äôs not, thanks god). The fried noodle is a bit bland and the yam chicken is not what we like.

Make sure you know a bit mandarin since they don‚Äôt have English menu and speaks little English.

One of the heavyweights in prata in Singapore.
Prices have increased noticeably after recent renovations, and now is queue-order and pay-first, but food quality seems to be fairly consistent (read: still good).

Parking will always be a huge deterrent to visits at this outlet, so come during off-peak hours!

The indian restaurant is hidden in the shop houses on the Phoenix hill opposite the Phoenix station. Carpark is available at a fee right in front of the restaurant. However, parking along the landed houses is also quite easy.

The place is neat and clean, and the staff is rather friendly and attending. We were recommended dishes based on our preference, and the food tastes really great as well. Naan is slightly over done with quite some burns, but overall quality of the meal is good. They also serve wine here if you are seeking some romance over dinner. It is well decorated for nice ambience.

Tandoori dishes are perfect, and would definitely try again in next visits. They also do delivery and work with deliverloo.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Teochew hand-made tim-sum, White carrot cake, Hokkien noodles, White chicken rice and Uggli muffins. Must try at each respective food stall serving only a single menu. Cannot miss them when you are at the food centre.
Delicious
Food is pretty nice. Yu Sheng was refreshingly different...  fresh salad leaves and 3 types of raw fish instead of the preserved stuff. No shell fish to trigger allergic reactions..
Katsu Don tasted sour to me and I don‚Äôt like it
Good food, good environment, good prices, friendly staff, won a truffle fries on lucky draw!
Good plate of fried rice. Just abit wet but the rice has strong wok hei. Pricing is very good. Love the chicken cutlet. Overall will be back!
Food took a while to come. Portion was quite small but food was tasty. Ordering using qr code was quite confusing. Set meal option wasn't elaborated in the website

Cheap and affordable and taste good as well. Don‚Äôt recommend the bubble tea though - taste weird.

For delivery, please be aware that the restaurant will take way longer to deliver than whatever is stated in the app. I took them an additional hour to deliver my food!
Good Satay beehoon
Good food! And amazing service:)

I've always enjoy the food from Sushi Tei. It's very fresh and they always have new seasonal items. today I had the lobster roll 1-for-1 because of UOB card promo, then a must have Kani Chawanmushi, with a piping hot Yosenabe. so good! ‚Ä¶
Great service and affordable prices

Garbage, even for a cheap Prata place.

One staff member sits by the safe entry and watches TV, the other little tyrant barks at you while you look for a QR code that they‚Äôve forgotten to put up.

Meat is absent from food. Everyone is made to sit in one direction so it feels like you‚Äôre eating in a prison camp.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content:
Nice to have an authentic Indian restaurant at AMK.
Food quality is amazing and service was fast.
Polite and friendly staff.

Great dim sum places

Brought my parents here for dim sum with chope 30% off vouchers. The food are great. I like their stir fried carrot cake with xo sauce and salted egg custard bao . Their dim sum are simple and great too. The tea is expensive (3sgd per pax).

However do note that they have a rest time at 2.30 pm so try to come earlier before 2.30pm as it will be the last order before the restaurant take a break.

Decided to finally give a review of this place. When it first opened few years back, the wait time for almost every food stall was long due to the crowd and the standard of the food was pretty bad.

However, I decided to give it a try again today with my friends, surprisingly everything we had improved in taste and wait time. Especially the Mee Hoon Kuey, the soup was tasty and not diluted like I had the previous time!

Overall, its not bad for a food court in a shopping mall. Will be back to try out other food stalls there too!

Limited tables available be prepared to  queue up and wait during dinner peak hour. Waitress are friendly and don't feel pressured to order fast and get on with life. Tried their signature crispy chicken cutlet, very crispy and nice, not oily too. The corn cob is a little soft and felt overdone but still alright.

Their tagline is "Possibly the best Rendang in Singapore" and I'm strongly inclined to agree.  I've never had better and it's a real treasure.  Bitter gourd is nice too, but the real star is the Beef Rendang.  Lovers of Texas-style BBQ will rejoice at this Rendang.
Be careful and double check of what you order either having there or take away. Good luck
Love the quality of food they served and their service is simply awesome! üëç ‚Ä¶
Friendly staff and good food!

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: The rice is nice and fragrance but a bit disappointed with the chicken as they are not tender enough. The price is on the high side compare to other shops. The chilli is nice but the ginger is dry and not fragrance.

Went there with my wife and 3 daughters, ordered their Signature Pan Fried Buns, XLB, Noodles With Spring Onion Oil and steam buns. The food is delicious which all of us like it. We will definitely visit again.

food is delicious as usual. refer to photos. restaurant seems to be understaffed, but they took our orders accurately n timely. Oh.. and a tiny cockroach crawled onto my side of the table and i smacked it with paper napkins. An eventful night for us üòÖ.

(Translated by Google) Many dishes. Noodle Soup Noodle Boil Noodle Rice Mixed Cake.

(Original)
Many dishes. Mee Siam Mee Rebus Lontong Nasi Campur Kuih Muih.
Food is average but service and ambiance good. Rather pricey. 1-for-1 corkage

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
Just sharing my opinion. Haven't been there for few years. Today, All food served cold. Not worth going anymore as it's totally different from years back.

Used to have second helping for the fragrance rice but it is now taste like raw flour. The Char Siew taste like you're putting sugar in your mouth as it's overlay sweet. The roast pork in the market taste way better than theirs. Ordered quarter Chicken but given all breast meat which used to be tender and tasty but not anymore.

All of the above is even more obvious when our "lie detector" didn't even finish half of his favourite fragrance rice ü§≠
(Translated by Google) Bought the prawn beancurd skin, and there were 2 flies on it ü§ÆÔøΩ ‚Ä¶

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Absolutely awful service. Sat for 20 minutes and no one came to take my order. Even walked to the counter to make my order but the guy told me to sit down and wait longer. Place was only half full. Never to return ever.
Helpful staff, friendly service, decent prices for portion size. Food is certainly not bad.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Pros:
1. Had a great dining experience. Staff are attentive, foods are fresh, taste good.
2. Love the basil chicken and tom yum clear soup base.
Will come back again for sure.

Cons:
1. Limited selections but definitely worth it with the on-going promotions.

You have to be there early for their satay. Their mutton satay sells out really quickly. Their mee rebus is delicious. In early May, they received an award presented by the World Gourmet Summit. Testament to their food is good. This is a very hardworking stall.
Good comfort food for an affordable price. This is definitely a hidden gem for me, my go to place for Indian Cuisine.

restaurant name: Chang Cheng - 531 Ang Mo Kio Avenue 10
content: The lady staffs is so rude and shouting with my wife after purchasing the food. So rude and still argue and I just told her off.

Place is kinda packed during lunch and dinner time. Food is not bad but a little too pricey. Went 2 times.

Ordered the glass noodles during my first visit. Not too sure why there isn't any sliced pork in it when it is clearly stated on the menu that there will be sliced pork. Ordered the jajang rice too. The looks of the jajang rice is pathetic. Just a plate of rice with a fried egg + the sauce. If I remember correctly the glass noodles is 18 dollars and the jajang rice is 15 dollars. Also ordered the sweet and sour pork. Pork hardness is inconsistent. A good portion of it was hard af and the rest were just nice. Can't remember how much was it but it's definitely more than 20 dollars.

Ordered jajang noodles the 2nd time I went. Not too sure what's the hype about. While I feel it does taste better than the average jajang noodles you can find in Singapore, it certainly isn't very special or unique. Also ordered some spicy garlic chicken. It's better than the sweet sour pork. Costs 35 dollars and it's not even the big size. It's small size which is meant for 2 to 3 pax.

Overall I feel this place is overpriced. Food taste slightly above average. But for the price I'm paying I'll be expecting more than just slightly above average.

Workers atitude is so horrible! I wanted to order Prata Tissue and they rejected my request as they told me they were busy with so many customers orders. And can't even make 1 piece of prata tissue üôÑ then after 15 mins sitting at the table while my family's food finished, I tried my luck again to order Prata Tissue as most of the customers has  leave the makan place, they accepted my order. How pathetic that is. And im complaining about prata tissue overall. Hahahaha

Ordered whole bunch of stuff for takeaway, including a pack of pappadum, 3 pieces inside. They took it to the kitchen for some reason.

When I open the pack of pappadum at home, there was only 1 piece inside. Perhaps the other 2 are in the pack of mutton briyani? Nope. It got taken out by them. Probably repacked and sold again. Come to think of it, my 1 piece of pappadum isn't as crispy as it should, it is a little stale, with a slight leathery texture.

While we are at it, mutton briyani's curry is waaaay too salty. 80% solid bone, 20% meat, tendon and fats.
My favorite roast duck place. Loved the dong bo rou too... Service has always been pretty good and food is served on time .

Well torched and polished meat. Not exactly mind blowing, but it is satisfactory - above average. Indoors (also ourdoors) are very well furnished and looks classy. Not exactly value for money (about 15+ for a bowl of Don), but acceptable for the quality. Crowd here is mostly working ppl

Food via delivery was always good, but somehow dining in turned out to be a horrible experience. Didn't take long for them to come up with our food but it came in cold for my friend and I with much lesser meat than usual.
Best to avoid dining in I guess.

First time trying this mexican food chain and I must say Im pleasantly surprised! Ordered from foodpanda but the food was still fresh! Got the mild nachos with grilled chicken. For $16, the price was quite expensive but it was really filling which was unexpected!! The guac was delicious too :) Will definitely try their tacos and burritos next!!
A few plates of meat for 2 pax, $90 and not even filling. Honestly just go for some random bbq buffet also more worth it

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Lovely food and good service. The lobster is very fresh and it is paired well with the sauce.

Promfet fish is fresh and we'll steamed (firm meat). The teochew style steam I think it's slightly too sour with the salted plums.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Tasty food, pricey but expected. Service was mediocre and the atmosphere was cosy. Went on a Sunday afternoon and it wasnt crowded. Decent waiting time of about 5-10mins. Well staffed.
This small restaurant surprises me. It serves very delicious and crispy prata with very tasty gravy too. The teh tarik at $1 is very nice too!

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: This is a clean and good place to eat at . Lot of choices and cleaner helpful .keep it up.Be the best .

Went at a colleague's recommendation to try during lunch. Didn't go for their daily lunch set and opted for their katsu curry rice. The curry itself is pretty good, generous. Squid was nice with the dip and the potato salad was not too bad too. My colleague had the yakisoba which was surprisingly quite delicious. Overall, a homely little place I wouldn't mind retuning to again if I'm in the vicinity. Otherwise, it's located at a pretty inaccessible place - best to drive there.
Nice place. Taste goog.
Tasty pork belly. Let's support these small businesses, don't keep going Malls or the international restaurant chains.
The ribeye steak is definitely one of the best in value and taste. Not a fan of pork but the pan seared fish is great too. Love the mushroom soup and it a must have item.

I have never eaten coin prata without sugar before and its the first time I hear them saying coin prata don't have sugar lol. Really disappointed with their service and attitude. Like literally think twice before buying their food.
Also, the fish curry has a weird taste.

This block 151 is a interesting place that provides good food like Kowloon dim sum and soi 19. This shanghai place which is at the opp end of the block from the coffee shop serves really good food. We ordered, xiao long pau and 2 noodles and it was really good. Will definately be back but we need to come only when we have 1.5hr as the wait can be pretty long during lunch time.
Flavourful porridge that was still warm even with takeaway. Love the crispy wonton skin they give with every order. Cam purchase a set with youtiao and drink also.
Ordered the kimchi sliced pork don. Pork is very dry and tough, and overly smoky. Not very palatable.
Eaten egg and plain prata here. Teh tarik with ginger is nice. Ordered mine with reduced sugar üòä
You can get tasty Indian vegetarian food

Our senior ladies' choir was invited to perform song item and join the Christmas dinner. The restaurant packed about four hundred guests. The food dishes were served promptly. Dishes well presented, adhered to menu of choice by Host. Service good, ambience decor pleasant. Stage and sound system set up available, as the venue  facilitate karaoke, a key attraction.
Delicious local food! But too tough to Chope seats!
Quick meat you can grill yourself with 2 sauces
Succulent chicken cutlet
Delicious and affordable.

Honest to goodness local fare. Always enjoy
Their traditional curry chicken with a slice of roti prata.  Other faves of mine include the dry laksa. And of cos, while waiting for your mains to be served, why not get an Old Chang Kee curry puff?

#cafe #cafesg #localfood #localfoodsg #rotiprata #chickencurry #oldchangkee #jedidiahtan
Food was great, especially the duck. Service was excellent too.

Ordered for delivery the Gam Heong Bee Tai Mak with prawns spicy and fried rice with pork chop.

The pork chop was not too well marinated and tough .

The bee Tai Mak was awesome and among the most tasty and filled with wok hei, definitely a must order !!!

Prawn paste chicken wings was well seasoned  was fried till crispy.
Wide variety of Shan Dong cuisine. Don't miss the steam dumpling and Xiao long bao there!

(Translated by Google) Sichuan restaurant on the 2nd floor of Amara Hotel in Tanjong Pagar.

Because there are many Japanese guests and Japanese companies around, there are many Japanese customers on weekdays. For those who don't like it, the less spicy food is cooked by Less Spisy and the shop.

Mapo tofu, boiled fish (very spicy) Crispy chicken is really delicious ^^

Kam Jia Zhuang is our family ta pao Zhi char place to go. It‚Äôs convenient Cus all we do is to call them up, ask them for specials of the day, pack and we pick it up. Place is usually packed on Saturdays. Value for money zhi char. Highly recommended dish : SEAFOOD CRABS with black pepper. Other zhi char dishes include prawnball with pumpkin sauce, lemon chicken, lala bee hoon ( very good) and Ha Cheong Kai ( Fried chicken wings ). Do give it a try. üêºüêºü§™‚ù§Ô∏è
I thought it had some decent wok hei. Nothing special but a bit better than the wok hay around the corner.
Decent food. Not great ambience and a lil pricey for the portion in school.
Poor quality food and service. Not worth the money!

I have been curious with this stall whenever I walked past, hence decided to make a trip down for lunch.
.
Must say i am slightly disappointed, wasn't as good as i had anticipated. I mean it is decent and is affordable. Ordered the #BeefSteakDon (SGD$10.90) and #KimchiSlicedBeefDon (SGD$6.90), both include a glass of tea. In my opinion, the kimchi slice beef don is more worth it.
.

Had the imperial streamboat, the small portion was very generous. Comes with raw slices fish on the side, with extra veg, mushrooms and fried eggs to add on the streamboat looks very rustic and authentic.

The staff was very attentive ans polite.

Overall this was a very good experience.
Delicious food and there is free wifi. Has a variety of food. Highly recommended to eat here.

The Damage (no drinks): S$25-40 for two

Unassuming little Chinese joint along Neil Road that specializes in wonderful ‚Ä¶

The menu selection here is pretty limited but having patronised many times over the past three years, I'm still happy with whatever they serve =) Xiao long bao is really nice, as well as the crispy pork strips. Love their beef soup noodles too.

As for service, it's a hit and miss depending on how busy they are. Yesterday when I was there some lady in the kitchen was scolding someone else at the top of her lungs for a good 30mins stretch, so if you can enjoy good food and block out tension vibes it's totally worth it! (= Remember to call and reserve a table to avoid disappointment!
Only thai milk tea is left, cafe latte not i. Stock already
Had a lunch at siam kitchen few days back. The staff are nice
Food was Super delicious, price was reasonable üëçüèªand their ambiance there was very nice with 90s style design.overall had a nice time and good food there, would go back again üòÅ
Mixed grill for $13 - waiting time was about 20 min. Pork and chicken was tender, but portion could be a bit more for the price paid in my opinion. Potato ball was interesting

Delicious and affordable Chinese food. The quality is comparable to many fancy restaurants, at a fraction of the price. Below $50 for 2-3 pax. Highly recommend the boiled sliced fish, potato salad and pig ears salad. I bought their frozen dumplings previously - which were very good as well.

It has been 3 years since I last visited Jack's place Ang Mo Kio branch. Love the tenderloin well-done texture. Comes in a set with oreo cheesecake but lobster bisque and cake standard has dropped. The lobster bisque does not taste lobster, the oreo cheesecake is not as good as other retailers cheesecake. Overall acceptable. As a cheesecake lover, i have tried so many places but given the price of the set meal, consider acceptable, not fantastic. The asparagus look pathetic.
Worst claypot chicken rice I've ever had. Just some pieces of chicken (with a lot of chicken skin), rice, and sauce being kept warm in a claypot. The rice wasn't even close to developing a crust.

Rude staff and lousy food with servings that is ridiculous. Ordered kimchi chicken soup that came with only 3 slices of chicken. Went to ask staff and she said "oh chicken is very little, u want more u add money if not then too bad" ridiculous
A great place to chill-out with friends and the food is very nice and authentic phillipinos cuisine.üëçüëèüôè
Great food as usual. From the century egg to wanton mee to crispy char siew bun and the fantabulous egg tarts, we couldn't get enough of it. Just a tad costly though

A favorite since I was a child. Delicious and value for money. My usual order with double chicken wing costs less than $5. The sweet sambal (Indonesia style?) is relatively unusual compared to the norm.

Only downside is that the coffeeshop is quite small, so you will probably need to takeaway most of the time.

North Indian food is quite expesnive here in Singapore but this restaurant serves you good food at fairly reasonable prices. It lives up to my expextations. The butter naan is the softest and probably the best that you can find in Songapore. Reastaurant staff is really nice, they serves you a range of mouth watering vegetables and kulfis.
The chicken and the chicken rice is ok. They should provide some drippings for take away I think. But staff is very friendly and professional. üòÅ

A place that worth a try!

Except for their ‚ÄòSalsa‚Äô, personally I find their salsa tomatoes taste are too strong, otherwise overall staff and food is great.

Hopefully get to try their truffle pork chop during our next visit. üòã

Have their claypot chicken rice. Overall is at the standard (ie presentation, taste-wise etc) but I would still prefer those heated using charcoal. Anyway, it‚Äôs a good to-go option if u miss eating the claypot rice!

Took away the coin prata and it was still crispy! It's a thin dough but it is crispy on the outside. Like their coin prata more than their normal prata.

Update: went back to dine in and tried their egg mozzarella prata (super cheesy, love it), hi-fiber prata (taste like normal prata but healthier) and iced teh tarik (very sweet, not so good). There's fish and chicken curry available but you have to scoop yourself. No paywave here. Cash, shopeepay and favepay only.
Food is good. portion is very generous. Served by friendly makciks would recommend others to come here to try their nasi lemak and nasi sambal goreng

the food is quite mediocre imo
the tomyum soup not spicy, not very tasty
the steamed fish like abit mushy
Have yet to try the other stuff..thosai is decent. Not much on the menu is available. Nice quiet place for a meal

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: A reasonable cut for the price you pay. It is probably not going to be the best steak you ever tasted but most likely not the worst too. Don‚Äôt get scared off the queue outside. They are just waiting to order before being seated. A good place to go for a family weekend dinner if you have always enjoyed the western food in hawker centre.

Food wise was so so, but staff was dishonest. Food is paid upon order and when my family and I left the place, they ask my father to pay again. I should have insisted a receipt upon payment. So people please beware.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Hearty thai food with value for money portion and personalised services!

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Food is nice and portion is good, price is reasonable and the staff there are quite friendly but sometimes slow in attending to us
The food was good. Most the food in the menu was not available. Had to order 3 times before I go to eat.

We tried a few of their dons including the pork belly, beef striploin, beef steak, Saba fish and a few of their skewers. Would highly recommend their skewers and the pork bowl and give the beef a miss as it was too overcooked and difficult to chew.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: If I stay nearby I will not mind having dim sum there.  Chicken feet is nice but a bit on the pricey side given that is a coffeshop setting. liusha pau was not too bad and the price was OK.

5 stars given for the excellent service provided. Service staff did inform us of a possible 10min wait time (was a Sat) but before 10mins they led us to use the VIP room instead. They were quick to provide utensils for my baby and food came relatively quick even though it was full house. Food from Jacks place was not as good as before, speaking from a regular since I was a kid. For example, the type of potato is not as fluffy and sweet that I recall and the boiled veges are quite tasteless. Still love their tea with milk and satisfied with the meal.
Decent food decent price! Great Beancurd noodles.
Good value nasi lemak sets! Blue pea rice was delicious! Love the beef rendang and fried chicken sets! Highly recommend!
Looking for a fish head curry takeout and tried it out here. Wasn‚Äôt disappointed. Both taste and price  ($30) were on point. The Assam had a real kick and fed 3 for dinner.

Food is decent, ordering is convenient.

The fried rice at ramen kiou is my fav.
Pork chop is very good. Not quite like the cheese over the veg, French fries is served hot but not crispy

Nice location, authentic food, good service.

The 2-3 pax black bean noodle set is truly sufficient for 3 men ü§§ Good value üëçüèªüëçüèª

The give pickles and kimchi for side dishes, but they tasted really good.
Staff were very friendly! Food was tasty too üòãüòã We had the steamed chicken and rice. Would recommend this place!
Very very rude the guy with tattoos.

Used to work for Genki sushi more than 10 years ago when I was still a student, even as customer, I often patronise them as the food was great back then. Recently went down to this outlet to redeem my birthday voucher only to then know about their app maintenance. Staff said they cannot use the voucher without the app and told me to email Genki Sushi to extend the voucher deadline. Thankfully, Genki Sushi understood my circumstances and agreed to extend my voucher deadline so that I may still enjoy a birthday discount. Will continue to patronise Genki Sushi with good extending customer service.

Extremely happy with the service served by Mdm Leong Tai Yoke.
She advised us not to under nor over order when we decided to go for the set lunch; as a result we ordered 3 pax set though we have 4 persons.
She‚Äôs also quick to help us to clean up our table and asked us if there‚Äôs anything we need and if we are happy with the serving and service.

Photo on menu looks delish. Actual dish plating looks üëå. Disappointed over the small bones in the rice and meat. Cabbage little off taste and black fungus not chewable.

Besides this dish, my colleagues commented that the food standards dropping. I will give my last round soon as I believe F&B needs supports.

Last year food was 5 star quality.
Seems like they had a change of chef..food is subpar now

Garlic Pork was tough

Ice teh diluted

content: Great service from Alfred Chia.  Personalised, professional and yet makes one feel so at home.  Dishes are still great standard (like before Covid).  If not for a bad customer experience with Veronica who ignored my help when I left something behind at dinner, I would have rated this restaurant 5*.
Price slightly high. Business pretty good though. Ordered the Kong Bak Pau  (10 for $24). Taste is good but the pork is very thinly slice. The Hong Kong noodles just too salty for me.
Nice..good service.. staff was very polite n friendly

The beef striplon is quite good. But i ordered medium rare but came medium. Supposed to minus 1 star from it. But the portion and balanced set meal has made it up. As for the lobster aglio oilo, was just very much average. But Will definitely visit again with the wide range of beef sets.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: This place serves very authentic Teochew dishes. Many of the dishes you don‚Äôt get to taste elsewhere! Brought my Teochew parent and they totally fell in love with the food here and walked out really happy!
Good quality ramen considering the price

Had an impromptu dinner here. Quiet, spacious place. Perhaps it‚Äôs a Thursday.

Service staff was polite and efficient. No hard selling or anything.

Ordered Indonesian pork (that‚Äôs the one in the claypot). It has a nice santan laksa taste to it. Perhaps it‚Äôs me trying it for the first time. There‚Äôs hae bee too, giving it a nice umami taste.

Minced pork with chai por tofu. Came totally drenched by the minced pork and chai por. Was nice except the saltiness came on stronger as you eat it.

Italian herb pork ribs. Not sure why I kept get reminded it‚Äôs salted egg.

Overall nice place for big groups. Food‚Äôs abit salty but I guess it‚Äôs bearable cos I like heavy flavours. ‚ó°Ãà

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: I have eaten many nasi lemaks in Singapore, but none of the nasi lemak can compare it to Malaysia.  This is the only nasi lemak I really feel it's so delicious!  The sambal is really spicy tho! It's better than Chong Pang Nasi Lemak. Will definitely return to order again!

Heard about this outlet during Ramadhan, and my long wait felt so worthwhile. Not only Mr Ramli is so patient and polite in attending to my queries. The food portion is huge and super value for money. Most importantly, its so delicious!! May your business prosper and more rezeki come your way.

Quality standard can vary.
Sometimes it can be charred or re-fried and masked by the sauce so that visually it seem fine.

Wondering is it because it was late night and they pre fried it.

Very fast service despite large number of customers yet the quality of the food is not at all compromised. I would even say this is the best McDonald's food I've ever had quality wise. Six ordering stands are available so service flows very smoothly. Fantastic experience
Nice ambience, good service, and fragrant chicken rice. Only missing part is there is no soup served together
The food is nice, especially the sauce. Seating places are limited, especially during this Covid period. Expect the price to be higher, given that it is located inside Northpoint mall.
The sambal stingray was great and the service was excellent, fast n efficient.

Chicken cutlet fried rice: Serving was generous, especially that of the chicken cutlet! Asked for less oil less salt to the fried rice and still found it flavourful. The chicken cutlet was really fried upon order so they came piping hot, which was great, but if they let the oil drain for a while longer I wouldn't have felt it too oily for my liking. I found that the rice used was more fluffy and moist than what I remembered of King of Fried Rice, so that's a plus.

It‚Äôs newly opened. Not all the items in the menu are available e.g thosa. Hope it will catch-up soon.
All the dishes are up to the standard and tasty.

Lovely interiors though it looks dark and foreboding on the outside. Service staff were polite and attentive on a Sunday lunch. Though there about 5 tables of guests, we were informed the restaurant was packed and dishes would take a while to come. Most enjoyable dish was the signature roast duck. Iberico pork cheek and Sichuan popcorn chicken were not excessively spicy. Efu noodles were pleasant and crabmeat egg white fried rice packed a nice flavour. Portions were small overall. The only dish that was underwhelming was the red bean pancake that was doughy and not crispy.
Crowded at peak hours.

Was here on 2 Aug 2022. This place has been here since early 90s if I remember correctly.

Weekday 2pm I wards this place is very quiet to have a good meal.
Bad attitude workers. Not worth paying for it. There are a lot better service and tasty indian food nearby.
Clean n cozy resturant.  Staffs services are very good and polite.  Foods wise are nice too..

Icy sweet and sour pork is the must try dish in the house. Nowadays you don‚Äôt find this dish easily in town.

‰∏âÊãºtrio bbq is also delicious.

Two things could have been improved from the service side.
- not enough baby chair
- we were seated near the kitchen window where cooked food are ready to be served. The kitchen still uses the loud speaker to play alert sound to the waitresses to fetch the dishes to tables. Could be very annoying with repeat alert.

The food quality can be better as compared to their competitor as some of the food items are really salty and portion are small/thin. The fried fish skin is not really appetizing as really tough when biting it...

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Looks tasty but decieving. Taste is too bland. And the fish meat noodle was fishy despite having such big slices of fish. Somehow the taste is lacking in all three famous dishes that u have ordered....

Good quality was ok-good. Hot drink portion was small given the price point. Definitely smaller than usual Coffeeshop glass mug quantity.

Service was-meh. The young gentleman mending the cashier counter was rude. I paid with a $50 note and he immediately told me ‚Äúgive me smaller note‚Äù. I had to explain that I just went to the ATM before he reluctantly accepted my payment.

The same staff also mixed up the order of another customer, giving her putih fried rice instead of merah. Customer was upset and mentioned that they should have asked instead of assuming that ‚ÄúChinese only eat putih, not merah goreng‚Äù. No attempt to apologize or to exchange the food, just insisted that it is as it is.
The teh tarik here is foamy and smooth. Not bad! But chicken briyani rice was cold, think they didn‚Äôt heat up, maybe can improve on this.

This mixed tofu is good, taste of lard. Salted vege soup is appetising to me. Vege is huge disappointed, too oily. I was there for Chinese New year dinner, their staple food like yee fu noodle and Vietnamese fried rice is good, but other dishes is horrible, fail in presentation and taste.

We ordered the poke bowl and paid about 15 dollars but it was outright inedible. The fish was tasteless and the rice was regular white rice. The rest of the toppings were okay because they were just shredded vegetables. The one star is for the staff, and the best part of the meal was leaving.
fresh healthy food in campus

surprisingly quite flavorful Stir-fried Beef Hor Fun. The beef cooked just nice , broth is richly aromatic. The ‚ÄúWok Hei‚Äù, heavenly. I believe they prepare the stock well, I am trying to figure out the ingredients though. Lol‚Ä¶. Fresh juicy crunch on the vege, cook just right, retaining the texture and moisture. Snow Pea could used a bit of prep work to remove the thin fiber string on both sides. Portion wise versus taste and price, I would say this is worth it. Would recommend sharing for smaller portion eater.

Red Tom Yum Soup with Seafood, less spicy. I would say the spicy, sour and sweet balance would suite most. I‚Äôll should take the original  spicy level though. A bit too sweet for me. Anyway, Shimeiji mushroom are yummy and have the fresh juicy texture. Squid and prawn wise prep & cook well, tender and juicy to enjoy. Can see the good knife works and skill prepping the ingredients. The chef really have some standards, I would say. The squid could have a smaller bite size cut though. Less chewing and bite with smaller pieces.

Overall, a delicious well balance flavored meal. Which is pretty rare. Yummy meal. I am surprised, in a good way.

Would recommend to try, while their food/chef/quality still in the season. ü§îüòÑ‚Ä¶

(written on 8 Mar 2022)

Seems like a regular weekend place for my family. My kids love this place. Simple place but great food. Their "Thosai" has gone a step higher in taste. Very good service by all of their staffs especially Mr. Rahim (hope I got his name right). My family of 6 are so routined that he knows exactly what we want. All the dishes are great and served hot.
