I always crave the prawn mee here. üòã Their lor mee is also very tasty!

Wasn‚Äôt very impressed. Service Staff seemed impatient, and were unknowledgeable about the food they were serving.

Had their Special Lamb Briyani too, but it was very underwhelming. It‚Äôs mostly bone. Maggi Goreng was terrible bland, almost like it‚Äôs just been cooked in water and drained.

Their Plain Prata was crispy, as promised. Plaster Blaster and Umami 50 were some interestingly delicious items.

The ingredients for Murtabak were not scattered evenly, so it was quite confusing with each bite.

Other than that, just a over hyped, and expensive place.
The porridge here is very good. Many varieties. Try the minced meat porridge. The set is additional $1.8 where you get one soy bean and youtiao. Goes well with the hot porridge

I LOVE THEIR CHILLI CRAB!!!

Delicious food!!!! Keep wanting more and more.

Recommended place to eat with your family.. Price is acceptable for delicious food.
Their mee hoon goreng is one of my favourite meals whenever i visited their premises.It is located in block 103 chong pang city.You should try them.

Obviously not interested in customer getting a good meal. Ordered nasi sambal goreng ayam makan and was given a prepacked pack on a plate. Food is cold and soggy. If I can give zero star, would have given it.  Food is tasteless too

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Their waiters have attitude problems and can't understand what customers want to order

I feel is a bit overrated on their claypot rice. But their san lao bee hoon is the high lite instead. The queue is seriously long. There is at best 15 tables indoor and 8 outdoor. The outdoor table is by a big drain, remind me of going to malaysia eating outdoor. Qing long veg feels normal. The garlic chicken also feel soso.
A nice japanese food street with stalls and also various japanese restaurants.  Good options if u like japanese stuff. sushi ramen yaktori etc.

Food was good, but on the expensive side. $6.50 for roast meat & char siew rice in a casual (not even food court) setting. 2pax, spent $19.50

Attitude sucks as we were carrying takeaway bread when we enter, and the cashier, shouted no outside food. Seriously, you really think we would buy bread just to eat at your small stall? Prefer to spend my money somewhere

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Wasn‚Äôt crowded when our family was dining in. Probably 5-6 tables occupied but kitchen couldn‚Äôt keep up with orders. Overheard countless conversations of wrong orders amongst servers. Service was also quite slow despite the small crowd size.

Impromptu decision to eat for dinner on a weekday. Only 3 tables as it‚Äôs getting late. Service was prompt and service staff was friendly.
Orders Patin fish, Trio eggs spinach, Scallion chicken and Ee fu noodles.
Most of the dishes were tasty and were up to standard. Ee fu noodles were fragrant, fish was fresh and chicken was well done and tender. The spinach could be improved though. A little bland. Soup was not thick enough.
Overall, I would come back again

Visited them almost every week over the last couple of years, but recently moved out of the North West area and so haven't had the time to pop by, but we definitely remembered them when it came to our catering choice for our housewarming. And they sure didn't dissapoint. Some of our guests even asked for their contact details. Definitely top notch food and always consistent too!

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Food is good, but the uncle always take wrong order, this is the 2nd times! Waste my time go back and change and not even an apologize from them. I hope no more 3rd times please.

The restaurant has been here for quite sometime. A little gem with many signature dishes e.g. the KL Hokkien Flat Noodles, Sour Vegetable Steamed Fish, etc. My favourite dish is the salted baked flower crabs, which is not commonly found in the restaurants. You can get really big and meaty ones if the season is right. Another dish I have tried is the baked bee hoon which is as good as it sounds. Another of their specialty is the spicy chilli belacan. Bona petit.
Want to give a 6 star review to the staff Alan, he was very helpful and friendly. Food was delicious.  Serving time was fast. Have a pleasant experience.
So many times recieved with burnt meat! Boycott this shop please!

Pastries are nice, but most things here are a bit more pricey than they're worth, in my opinion.

I'd add this to my list of places in Katong you should try, but not necessarily one you'd want to frequent.
Dont have many things despite having a menu. Staff kinda rude

Nasi Lemak burger is back and the taste is good. McD is Super popular and there‚Äôs always a line so expect waiting time. The people behind the counter work hard and are happy to help. Having eaten here so many times, the error rate isn‚Äôt worth mentioning and their diligence is definitely appreciated.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Closest South Indian food you can get near Central.Decent price.

Above average western food stall at a coffeeshop.
Ordered Pan fried Dory fish $7.50.
Not oily. Very well presented
Ask for pepper sauce to be on the side, Broccoli is well cooked. Coleslaw is made by themselves.

Exceed my expectation for a coffeeshop.

Always enjoyed the Peking duck here. The platter with all the sauces and condiments is something which we  don‚Äôt see in other restaurants. Restaurant was very busy during our visit and service was a bit slow but overall, we had a good time. Will visit again.
Nice foods especially the pig trotter jelly and the braised duck.
Mushroom soup slightly watery but tasted decent. Ribeye steak tasted great for its price and was nicely cooked. Fries were very crispy. Chocolate brownie was amazing. Would return again.
The prata is crispy and delicious. Did not quite enjoy the meeting goreng. Usually a queue to get in but moves fast.
Love this restaurant, but removing 1 star because they removed my FAVORITE DISH - the fried knife cut noodles with Beef!!!!!!! Please bring it back :(

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Food was great and price performance ratio was good. Thoroughly enjoyed my meal:) Hotpot base was nice and also was something unique. Highly recommended and definitely will return

A shout out to new service staff Aiman for being kind, prompt and friendly when serving our table. We were really appreciative of him attending to us.

Meanwhile, appreciate if the management of Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot can look into the performance and conduct of service staff, Margaret. Throughout our 1.5 hour session dining at your restaurant, Margaret was bossing and instructing all your service crew around to clean tables, serve other tables while she herself practically contributing nothing at all for the entire duration.

When making payment, we feedbacked the above to the manager on duty. He mentioned the following
1) Prior complaints have been received against Margaret by both service crew themselves and customers.
2) Margaret is a service crew, similar to everyone else, and not a manager etc. Hence, logically, she should be taking a fair share of the workload

Hence, hope that management is able to look into the above, please.

Everything is pretty bad including the drinks. Only the curry is nice actually.
I think they cant handle big crowds and just rushed to get the order out asap. Wouldn‚Äôt recommend at all. First and last time coming here.

Nice place to chill out with local delights.
Good selection of beers at reasonable prices

Great ambience and food. They boast no MSG in their food, even the sauces are made from scratch. Highly recommended items include Beef Tenderloin Cubes and Stir Fried Meesua. Try their cocktails too. They have pretty unique concoctions. More reviews on my IG : @zanthrea.
Very warm poor ventilation

Ichiban is not the cheapest dining option around, but it certainly delivers in the set menus in my opinion. Simple, casual setting over some delicious food, sounds good to me!

Always a fan of their salmon don, will always request for an extra serving of sesame oil and chilli padi for that extra kick. Unagi is thick and lathered with sauce, accompanied with egg and rice. Soft shell crab is a hit as well, crispy and flavourful.

Overall, always a great time dining at Ichiban! :)

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Good food. Welcome to Ang Mo Kio

Selection of food was a little small although most of the sticks were only priced at $1. Cooking of the food was really quick and the skewers below totaled up to $12. Taste wise, food was very decent although a pair would probably need to order more than pictured to be full. 4 types of sauce selections were offered. Generally a decent joint although i probably would not make a special trip for this.

Definitely my favourite Hotpot Restaurant with individual pot of soupü•∞. U can share a pot for 2 pax too. All the ingredients are really fresh and most importantly, have tried about 4types of their soup base so far and it's all been really yummy especially tomatoüçÖ base. #msgreedysis #greedybuddiez
Overpriced and food quality is bad, their xiao long bau and siew mai taste like some frozen section products and re-sell it to customers at a higher price. Would not come back again
The staff super bo chap and rude, I just left the shop without ordering anything.

Many many thanks to Ash, Ady and Alexis for the great hospitality. Always feel so welcome @ Malayan Council and food, as always, is amazinggg! So if you are a foodie and an Instagram addict, this place is for you, people!
Awesome Samsui Chicken. Visited 2 decades ago, tasted the same. Except the ginger paste slightly less salted. Well done.
Place offer nice spread of Heng Hua style foods. Not bad considering the price is very reasonable for zi char style. Worth a try and repeat visit
At least this place have a decent sushi. Try to avoid lunch time or dinner time. Always long queue. Price on a high side . Can be cheaper
Tamako is run the way a warm-hearted Japanese mom would: with simple, authentic dishes. Really enjoyed the Hokkaido grilled squid and unagi sushi.

Very nice Ambiance and the food was Excellent , we had the mutton gravy , murtabak , roti-john , pepper prawn, sati soru - and platter - all tasted delicious!!!  The chef was very efficient in getting the order ready:)
Feedback for the service crew: Base on your seating capacity and staff strength I think you can render even better service , food arrives faster than the beverages and there could be more proactiveness from the service staff. Secondly I know the F&B sector is moving towards digitalization in terms of food ordering and QR code scanning but to a certain extend service staff can still hold onto a device to take 2nd and adhoc orders from customers as there should still be some level of tolerance towards manual food ordering.
But it is still a 5 STAR* because "Good food don't go wrong" and I am sure you will rectify your service in future.

I used to like Ichiban Boshi, but i am so disappointed this time. The ika yaki (grilled squid) is so small, it is so different from what I ate last time, and from the menu too. This is the first time (in my memory) that I immediately complained to a waiter on their food. That waiter called a lady and immediately they took it away. 10 minutes, the lady sent back the ika with additional few more pieces (the whiter ones in the left of the picture) and said they added more for me, then mumbling that it is 150g while walking away...

The taste is different from Japanese grilled squid, but more like a sambal sotong.

I am disappointed with the food. Wondering if this is  single case issue, or overall the standard of this branch dropped..

2nd time coming back after a few weeks. 1st experience was not good. Maggie goreng doesn't taste good. This time order prata, got my order wrong, banana prata became onion prata, despite having the receipt. Fish curry is too salty. Seems like they have a habit of getting orders mixed up or wrong. I missed the Malaysian indian cook and the local abang Malay guy who makes good teh tarik and teh halia

Best ramen! Authentic Japanese ramen with rich broth and generous servings. Free x1 serving of noodle but I think it‚Äôs not needed as they already gave a generous portion of noodle in the soup. Highly recommend and will definitely come again!
Had a satisfying dinner here.
Friendly and nice staffs! Fun time gathering! Will definitely come back again!

Had late lunch here with my boyfriend and was pleasantly surprised to be served by Peggy, a very chirpy staff :) she ensured we had seats and checked in on us from time to time if we needed anything. Kudos to the team's training and upholding standards to good customer service

Haha thought this was a bistro but turned out to be a seafood foodcourt with zhi cha stalls and a row of kebab and western food. Went on a Saturday evening and place had a big turned out of customer. Ended a bit disappointed as was hoping to have a quiet place to dine. Food also took >30mins to serve.
Karens rude service available here! No price tag!  Get rude service and mystery prices here!
I ordered fish soup here. Fish is fresh and big piece.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content:
Worse prata ever. Curry is diluted and the Maggie Goreng is worse.
Standard drop tremendously, will never eat here again

This is one place where the food is as authentic as it gets! Nice ambience and even nicer staff makes this a go-to place for anyone who wants to taste what spicy indian food really tastes like. It ain't over the top, but don't say I didn't warn ya
standard drop alot. been patronise for 2years and today will be the last. sirloin steak is the hardest i ever tried in my life for medium well. side dishes are ok still.
CKT looks nice but was pretty bland, generous with the beansprouts thou.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Food was pretty good but some dishes were pretty expensive.

A portion of chives + scallops was $60+

Tot the best dish was the cai Po Hor Fun

(Translated by Google) Best Nasi Lemak ever! Chicken wing was juicy and tasty and hand-made Peanuts & Ikan Bilis and Achar were yummy. You can choose different level of sambal chili. I took with blue coconut rice, Kukus Kerabu. Beautiful presentation and hospitality of the store owner was the reason of my recommendation! There are 3-4 outlets on the island, but Nasi Lemak is here! Is recommended. SG5-6th place ~

(Original)
Best Nasi Lemak ever!    Chicken wing was juicy and tasty and hand-made Peanuts & Ikan Bilis and Achar were yummy.   You can choose different level of sambal chili.  I took with blue coconut rice,  Kukus Kerabu.  Beautiful presentation and hospitality of the store owner was the reason of my recommendation!   „Ç¢„Ç¶„Éà„É¨„ÉÉ„Éà„ÅåÂ≥∂ÂÜÖ„Å´3‚àí4Â∫ó„ÅÇ„Çä„Åæ„Åô„Åå„ÄÅNasi Lemak„Å™„Çâ„Åì„ÅìÔºÅ„Çí„ÅäÂãß„ÇÅ„Åó„Åæ„Åô„ÄÇ„ÄÄSG5-6‰Ωç„Äú
Not proper response when order threw online food delivery.

Tried Set C which consisted of the jjajangmyeon, jjampong(seafood noodles) and tangsuyuk (sweet and sour pork)! 3 of us shared the set and food portions were definitely sufficient. Liked the jjajangmyeon and tangsuyuk the most; the jjajangmyeon sauce was savoury enough but not too jelat, and the tangsuyuk was nicely fried and went great with the sticky sweet and sour sauce! Will definitely come back again :) the kimchi was great too - crunchy texture and really good seasoning

have ordered a couple of rice dumplings with abalone, unfortunately the nice pyramid packaging was run out.üò™

it was peppery but it was big with lots of different ingredients and it tasted great overall!  recommended!  shall buy more next year!! üòã
Visited once. A very average Western food stall. Dislike the coleslaw, tastes very watery, the sauce not coated on the vegetable. Meat is small piece and taste very normal...

one star purely cause prices are on the lower side. else probably 0 stars to be given. food was BAD. tried twice and both was equally bad. food generally tasteless. no idea why people are queuing for this was the food is terrible. food from the veg rice shop is way better and cheaper.
The service is very slow. For the pricing, we can get a better taste at another place.
Very nice Thai restaurant. Lavishly decorated with flowers. Friendly service and some very nice food. I always come here for lunch if work brings me to the neighborhood.
I ordered Vegetable kottu parrta really it was tasty , they added appropriate vegetable with kottu. I enjoyed it
mac & cheese sides are really good

Above average zi char, not spectacular. Price are 10%-15% higher than your neighbourhood zi char. Have been eating here since young, and still having it often. If u stay in jurong or changi, not worth travelling down tbh. I personally love the sambal fried rice, give it a go!
Valued for money and their sauce for their Lok Lok are great!

Ordered prawn been hoon soup. And had to agreed with another sharing the table that the soup is superb but could give more, quite a lot of prawns given but quite bland in taste. Not sure if the dry version is a better choice

Use to go  once a while for Nasi champoo and or Nasi Padang
2)When  it s past 1pm (due to its strategic position for food)*i  visit to eat comfortably in air con; food s spicy

decent cafe
Price slightly on the high side but still ok
Food is good but salmon set, portion slightly too small
Recommendation: Double Chocolate Brownie, Big Breakfast n the tea series

Delightful Experience To Your Tastebud and Pocket. Try The upgrade ($1) from Donburi To Bento Set

Teriyaki Chicken Donburi 4* - Decent portion of chicken meat with tasty teriyaki sauce. Though chicken texture can be more tender. Goes well with the rice.

Bento Set 4* - 1 well fried carrot tempura, small portion salad in Mayonnaise and a bowl of hot, well flavored savory miso soup. Crispy fried tempura batter (yummy with teriyaki sauce) was given for my teriyaki bento set.

Value for $$ + 0.5*

Simple place with home cooked feel Indian food.
Their claypot rice series real standouts and the briyani meals flavourful. Be prepared to wait for the claypot rice. Pricing wise is pretty reasonable considering the huge portions. Good for sharing with others unless you have a big appetite. Only downside to the location is the limited parking places available along the drive way.
Rojak serve cold  and all cut in big size. Service is worst, ask for you tiao rojak but given big plate rojak. Kopi is like drainage water, not much Kopi taste.

Weekday order 1pm, 2 teh aliah and 1 mee goreng. Ordered spicy mee goreng so i can only assume he adhered to my request by sprinkling some chili padi. Taste of mee goreng is mediocre, tea was a little sweet. Waiting time is long by normal standards. Total damage $8.60! I presume tea costs $1.80 each.  Meegoreng 5$. Same price as Adam Road or Newton. At least the one in newton come with a sunny side up.. not coming back again unless price is on the signboard.
Good service! Price is slightly higher as compared to other Yakiniku Restaurant but still affordable and worth it.

Always had queue when we passed by, finally got to try Sushi Go on a Monday noon...
Free wifi so everyone can order from the online menu. Our total bill was $56plus for 3 of us. Food is fresh and served quickly.

Interesting little Rojak outlet. Price I feel is reasonable and the food is fresh and hot when served. The source is less nutty then usual but still well made.  While the place is a bit dirty I must say but you should try the food still. The cashier is quite is a funny guy üòÅ
Curry a bit watery, not that crispy n dough too thin. For small eater is good
The best halal japanese food in Singapore by far!
Excellent  Service  and food is of high quality and portion for small is good size . Staff very helpful  n patience. Will come back again. Keep  up the excellent standard. üòé
The pork ribs herbal Italian is good. Prices are reasonable. Food is yummy!
Decent price point and varieties to choose from. Ordered thru QR code and the food will be delivered right in front of you via the 'train'.
The service is good.

Qtr roast duck=$17. Mixed char Siew & roast
Meat=$16. One braised egg=$1. Noodle kosong=$2. White or chicken rice=$1 each. Total damage= $38 for 3 paxes. Price on the high side but the quality of their char Siew and roast duck is good & above average.

Was skeptical about this place initially as it was introduced by one of our friends who sometimes make poor choices when deciding on food places.
She has proved us wrong this time.

Ordered a few dishes that evening, and the 2 dishes that left a deep impression was the Jajangmyeon and the sweet and sour pork. Super tasty! The first thing we complimented was not the food but to our dear friend who chose this place for dinner.

We did not have to wait too long for our food to be served. Service was excellent and the staff were very attentive to our requests.

As a local food critic, I will rate this place 9.43 out of 10 (give face abit and rounded up to 5 stars in this review). Highly recommended üëç

Authentic Thai taste + value for money price point, makes this place a winner, beating the Thai restaurants found in malls. Queues are common at the usual peak hours and a 30min queue (at least) is expected, no reservations are accepted. The down side is the lack of white regular lots as the car park is 95% red lots 7pm onwards. Check out the pics I took as we had a spread of dishes!
The new waffle stall is awesome. Strong pandan favour and chunky thick waffle. Available spreads are peanut, blueberry, durian, butter etc. some are hotdogs too. Opens till 9pm ++.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Best Mookata in tpy area! üëçüèªfriendly staff and service is really good too. Initially my fiance and I ordered ala-carte.

Upon serving all of the food, one of the male staff (a little big size) came over and told us if we would like to change to buffet instead as it would be much more worth it. We're glad that the staff was kind enough to inform us.

Would definitely go back again.

We were there on a Saturday at about 7pm. There was a short but constant queue. Order was fast and wait time reasonable.

We ordered the Hot Plate Combo Grill, which has beef, pork, chicken, bacon, sausage, coslaw, egg and fries. Fries and pork were quite good and the rest were pretty normal. But for $10, there is really nothing to complain.
Delicious duck roasted with angelice herb üëçüëçüëç

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: I and my friends(4pax) went there to have dinner. We ordered Kothu Parata and Tea Halia. Kothu was not hot enough. Mutton Rogan Gosh was not enough portion for the price. They gave 3 Tea Halia and the waiter forgot one tea halia. Later he brought another which tasted like hot water. We didn‚Äôt feel good service here..

Went to this Tim Sum place this morning.The place did not seem to be that crowded. So we sat down and tried to get the waitress'  attention to make an order .The waitress indicated for  me to wait. But for what? She walked  up and down the restaurant as though she was  very busy. Got fed up with  the service and walked  out..i wonder whats wrong with this place. Anyway sorry to the boss for having such workers.. your loss for not training them about customer service..
By far the best Lok Lok I have eaten in Singapore. Far better than the famous that the DLLM LOK LOK that need to queue for 2 hours.. 100% worth it

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
Used to be great. Now after the menu changed, food is cooked differently too. Usual nice food replaced with questionable combinations of food, options are too limited. Signature homemade barley was also removed. Overall, dropped from the expected 5 star experience from Crystal Jade to 3.

With high prices and a reputation to uphold, I expected way better.
Their serving time was super super super slow. The food taste average only and they are charging their food so expensive. NOT WORST VISITING. FOOD NOT NICE!!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Fresh ingredient at a reasonable and affordable price. Definitely will come back again.

Ok fish ball noodles, soup base smells nice but abit salty for me. Good portion of noodles.

However might not be worth the queue

Surprised to try delicious Thai food hidden between HDB blocks in the heartlands. Recommend to try their green curry and their salted egg chicken! The food came quite quickly and the portions were just nice for a family of 4. Place was packed so we had alfresco dining and realised there was another space they had a few stalls down. Don‚Äôt expect good or friendly service for a place like this but come for the food! Decent price for quality taste :)

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Probably the best Hunan food in Singapore

Very nice and fresh food, with good price.
No beer or any kind of alcohol allowed though.
Authentic thai food with excellent service!
Had dinner with friend here. The food is decent, given the price. High value for money if you are just craving for noodles or dumplings!

Ordered Set C, which consisted of Tangsuyuk (sweet and sour pork), Jjajangmyeon(black bean sauce noodle) and  jjampong (spicy seafood noodle).

The sweet and sour pork was too oily, we ate two to three pieces and it was too ‚ÄòJelak‚Äô for us. The pork was also not crispy and not appetising, the whole dish was ways off‚Ä¶.

The Jjajangmyeon has only onion and nothing else, it was also too greasy. The jjajangmyeon tasted and looked like those packaged Jjajangmyeon you can find in the Korean food section in Cold Storage. There are other restaurants in Singapore that serve much better Korean black bean sauce noodle than this shop.

The spicy seafood noodle was also a huge disappointment. The soup tasted like instant noodle soup. We ordered ‚Äòseafood‚Äô noodle but there was no seafood at all, there were only three pieces of cured squid pieces with lot of onions. The noodle was also not authentic and not freshly made.

Definitely, will not visit this shop again. My advice to the owner or the cook is to go thru the YouTube, there are many channels that teach people how to cook simple Korean food. Please learn from these channels on how to cook proper Jjajangmyeon and Jjampong.

Had the 1 for 1 deal. Chicken chop was nicely seasoned & tender, while the baked potato with sour cream & bacon bits were pretty yummy too. Hard to fault at this price. Lost a star due to dated & old furniture. But tasty food comes first of course.

Sadly on our 3rd visit on 12 July, the sizzling hot plate was no longer sizzling, and food was served lukewarm only. Wife couldn't even finish her plate, which she usually can. What a letdown that standards have dropped so quickly. Dropped to 2 stars from 4.

It‚Äôs a great experience. The ambiance is very welcoming and charming. Amazing food and service. A staff by the name of danish i met there was extremely friendly,knowledgeable and make great hospitality during my dining. Highly recommended.
Good and tasty food.... And the promo is quite reasonable

Nice place to eat beef-don..the beef is cooked properly and very well seosoned..the price is slightly high and the portion is quite small..however the ambience is good while we enjoyed the dinner..came back for several times whenever we have no idea what to eat..
Best old school western food ever eaten, at hawker, succulent pork chops, 6 stars

Location: Nestled between some high profile eateries, so you won't miss it. You may find it hard to find parking space during peak hrs, so come early to avoid the stress.

Menu: A decent variety of japanese food, whipped up by a legitimate Japanese chef. You can read abt the history of the shop on the menu itself. Have attached some images for reference.

Waiting Time: Approximately 15 to 20 mins during peak hrs.

Quality of Food: Homemade, heartwarming Japanese food. Decent considering the price factor! Delicious.

Overall: Value for money Jap food that is worth coming for.

Authentic Hakka food with generous serving and warm hospitality. Their food are homemade dishes that will warm the cockles of your heart. The boss treats customers like friends and ensures that they are well taken care of. Would recommend making reservations on weekend as they would be packed.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content:
Fresh food.
Thick sambar.
Pocket friendly.
Light on stomach.

Coffee could have been better.
Service could have been lot better. Know how to handle the pressure please.

My first visit! We didn‚Äôt want to shell out a lot for some western food and came across this value-for-money, old-school joint. The chicken cutlet is one of the best I‚Äôve had recently, tender on the inside with a crust that is crisp and not bready. The coleslaw, baked beans and fries were fresh and tasty. The tenderloin steak was juicy; medium rare finished perfectly to a pink centre on the nostalgic steakhouse style hot plate . Will be back! Note that they‚Äôre moving to TPY Lor 1!
Amazing malay dishes! Plenty of traditional kuih available and friendly staff. Recommended!
Nice promo , nice food came back twice already. Their service is on top too‚ò∫Ô∏è

I would like to take this opportunity to thank your staff (90787 Lee Yoke Chan) of the Northpoint branch.

We knew the crowd on a Sunday (15th May 2022) and we expect queuing for a while for a table of 10 pax for our 1st family dinner in 2 years.  After staying in the queue for 30 mins, Mdm Lee received us at front of the queue. She informed us that we will need to wait for around 1 hour plus as the restaurant had only 2 rooms with table that could accommodate 10 pax. She was very polite and even apologised for the long waiting time, as there was another family of 10 infront of us waiting for a table.

At around 7.30PM, Mdm Lee asked us if we would like to have a split table 5 + 5 as she wasn‚Äôt sure how long more we will need to wait for the next room. She was kind enough to offer us this arrangement as we were already waiting for 1.5 hour. We agreed to the arrangement, and while we were preparing to order, we noticed that the customer that was in the room had completed their meal and is leaving the room. Hence we asked Mdm Lee if we could change our table to the room. She kindly agrees to our request. We were told to wait outside the restaurant while she worked to clear the room for us.

While waiting outside, we heard that the other customer behind us (also with 10+ pax) shouted at Mdm Lee. They were unhappy that the room was given to us as we had already accepted the split table. They accused Mdm Lee of being unfair and they continue to hurl accusations, insults in Mdm Lee to the verge of tears. I am writing this feedback to clarify these points;

(1) Mdm Lee is acting professionally, and even so after continuous accusations and insults from customer

(2) Mdm Lee tries hard to accommodate request and provide solution to us and the other customer

(3) Mdm Lee do not deserve the insults and accusations made against her

(4) We were given the room because we were next in the queue and made the request to Mdm Lee

(5) We heard the other customer will be complaining against Mdm Lee, we would like to provide our side of the story

(6) We would like to thank Mdm Lee for her professionalism and apologise to her for the inconveniences caused to her
Their signature noodles is nice. The wanton and dumpling are tasty and generous portion of prawn for that price! Worth to try.

Amazing Roast Duck. Heavenly proportion of crispy skin, just enough fat underneath the skin and juicy meat!

The restaurant is beautiful too!
Must try will be the sesame oil chicken soup. 2 levels available with good aircon environment.
Marinated soft egg really good. Other than that, nothing else worth mentioning. Ramen broth incredibly salty. Salmon just sauce with rice, nothing special.

At last get to try this Hakka restaurant. Ordered a set for 4 at SGD48. Really worth it. Taste is close to original Hakka village claim by grandma. Do book early to avoid disappointment. Am lucky to walk in n have a seat.

Has frequently visited this Centerpoint Malaysia Chiak for Penang Laksa and Prawn noodle. The usual auntie is very friend, however today there's a new very fatvyound punk was not. Ordered a big bowl Penang Lakes, this fat guy gave soup just barely cover the noodle. When I ask him little more soup,  he told me I cannot give more,  this is company policy, if you want more you'll need to pay for the soup. Sorry I cannot help you. Wth? I wanted to give 1 star,  but luckily the other senior staff who came back from outside and I asked him for little more soup he top it up without any hesitation. This is the first time I've ever encountered such situation after coming here like 2 years plus, probably my last visit here. :(

Don't know whether they get their friends help with the Google review. Order 6pc Xiao long bao + soup spicy soup. Taste like microwave food  and even worse than kopitiam food. It costs me 18+. Very expensive. Very long waiting time although it is not peak hour.

Better to go DTF or other Chinese restaurants.
OCK is no longer only serving curry puff and fishball. They selling coffee, mee Siam, beehoon and many more. They even have sitting area. üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª
The nasi lemak is really so so only. The young man behind the stall is rude & unfriendly. A waste of stomach space, time & money.

Unsure if the worker‚Äôs there were lying or telling the truth but apparently they told me that they dont accept CDC voucher‚Äôs as mode of payment.

This is completely misleading as there is a sticker of CDC voucher pasted at the wall right beside the cashier, which made me question the honesty of the worker‚Äôs here as well as  the boss. Besides that food takes time to serve during weekends and thay you have to be upfront and vocal about your order in order to place an order.

To end off, Customer Service is at an all time poor üëéüèª
Enjoyed this quaint  northern Chinese restaurant in Balestier.  Worth the travel!

EXCELLENT FOOD, LOVELY OWNERS & EXCELLENT PRICE !

I stumbled upon this coffee shop this morning !

Ordered mee siam for breakfast and packed lontong home for lunch !  Paid $3.50 each !  Excellent price of $7 for 2 meals.  Totally worth it !

The owners did not short-change on their ingredients despite the price.  I did not ask the owners but I believe they made their gravy from ground up and their ingredients are all fresh !  Very favourful and yummy !  No regret !

I will definitely come back and try other food made by owners.  I enjoy and appreciate ethical stall owners like this couple !

Thank you very much !

enjoyed the fried basil chicken rice. spicy and crispy enough for dinner for one. there was a bit of waiting involved as the chef cooked each dish individually but fortunately they have a buzzer system.

will return!

Used to be my top prata go-to choice since it opened more than 10 years ago. However, quality has dropped drastically in recent years which prompted me to write this review after giving this place one too many chances to redeem itself. Last time, if anyone asked my fave prata I would say Casuarina. Sad to say, this is no longer the case.

Went a few times on weekdays & weekends brunch, and prata served was cold as it is bulked produced to keep up with the crowd dropping by from their morning exercises around the area. Even with this, service can be slow and inconsistent i.e., other people who ordered after you getting their pratas served first. Imagine waiting for 15 to 20 minutes only to get your pratas served cold to you.

Wanting to avoid having cold prata served to us again, we decided to strategise and go during non peak i.e., dinner. This time prata was served hot (thank god) as it was made to order BUT all the currys incl the curry/dal for the dosai we ordered was cold. They just can't get it right anymore.

What a disappointment. Its only downhill from here for Causarina if they continue to rest on their laurals and depend on their once good reputation.

There are much nicer prata, and prata curry around the area worth your money instead i.e. Al Rahman Banana Leaf Indian Muslim Food at block 603 Ang Mo Kio Ave 5, or Sin Ming Prata at Upper Thomson. All the prata and prata curry is served hot. Theres also much depth to the prata curry!

Ordered their 4-5pax delivery menu. Food came within the delivery window however it was not kept in a warmer bag when it arrived. Food were cold and unpleasant to eat. They could have at least make an effort to keep it in a warmer bag. 2 stars for their delivery. 5 stars for their dine in.
Still that good ol' taste. Well marinated and juicy but their chicken chop seems to have shrunk in size. While the chicken cutlet now are as big as the plate it came on.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Soup base tasted like instant soup paste. Menu pricing too complicated to understand. Don't be too deceived by their advertising photos.

Not that it was bad, but on Sat at 11:45am the ordering kiosks already switched to the lunch menu. For some strange reason we couldn‚Äôt find the Happy Meal as a selection, I‚Äôm not sure if it‚Äôs because it‚Äôs on NTU campus? The line moved relatively fast but it still took us 20-25 minutes to get our order as there were tons of people.
It is quite rare to see any stall selling Sirloin steak for only $12. Gave it a try and it was worth the money. Meat was tender and juicy, and the sides were equally good. Will be back again. üëç

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Decent western fare at economical prices. Most meals include 2 side dishes for you to choose. For an extra $5 they will throw in a large bottle of SNAPP juice and a soup with garlic bread. This outlet is always crowded at peak hours so it's good to come a little early. I enjoyed the thick lucious black pepper sauce slathered over the chicken chop which was peppery and appetising.
Nice Rojak!!! The gravy is superb and food is fresh. Something to try when you r not in the mood to choose something. Simple food but delicious.

Been a regular there as food is good at the place. But, there are important things to improve on (especially lately).

Have been there since pre-covid, it‚Äôs a simple cozy place. Food is affordable, tastes authentic and very delicious, always enjoyed going there. But recently, it has been disappointing on more than 1 occasion.

On all of these occasions, it‚Äôs the same problem - service. Somehow they hired someone new (note: the last time we went, she‚Äôs not new anymore. She should have been working there for close to half a year already). This specific staff always got our order wrongly, either forgetting one of the dishes that we ordered, serving dishes first to those that came in later or once even, serving our dish to the wrong table. The people from the table were unaware and touched our bowl. When we pointed that out to the respective staff, she took the bowl from them and passed it directly to us.

In a situation like this (especially when it‚Äôs covid period), shouldn‚Äôt she change the bowl to a new one before serving it to us? It‚Äôs basic hygiene standards. And when we pointed out that we were not comfortable with eating from the bowl that other people have touched it already, she and the kitchen staff started shouting back and forth in Thai language in front of us. And the kitchen staff even banged the table at the counter more than once while shouting or complaining. At certain point, even glaring at us. As if it‚Äôs our mistake.

Ever since then, I have never felt comfortable going back again. I really hope they improve on this staff issue. It‚Äôs such a waste when their food is really good.

Just a note, I have tried giving chances and returned to patronise the store after I noticed the drop in their service. But it just gets worse every time. We also patronise around near 8pm when crowd is slower. This didn‚Äôt happen when it was busy.

And no, I do not expect very good or impressive service. But just simple service like getting our food right, proper hygiene and proper manners.
Nice ambience with good variety of food. The  vegetarian carrot cake is good. Tried their Tom yum fried kway tiao and fried Laska.

Order fried bee hoon without taugeh but still put taugeh & order sambal fried rice & nasi goreng kampung didn't mention never put vege but came very with vege.
Nasi goreng kampung taste like normal fried rice.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: This dim sum is worth more than a 3 star. Always have a lot ppl especially on weekends. Usually will be full house on weekends as early as 9am.

Waited 15 minutes from 1.15 to 1.30 and no one serve us to the table. Other patrons also chasing for their food. Both the kitchen and waiters are short of staff and its just normal weekday lunch at 1.15! A bit unacceptable. In the end the waitress say if we cannot wait, then better not eat in so we left. Disappointed..if you are not ready for service, say in advance. Or otherwise get more staffs to cover during the lunch hour.
First time at this branch. Food as usual nice. Nothing to shout for though.
Small outlet extended from nearby kopitiam food court, easily accessible and serves decent Indian vegetarian dishes from both north and south Indian varieties
The prata was served hot and fast.Tatse is nice.The teh tarik is not bad too.

Food is great and affordable at $1/stick.
Staff are friendly and service is fast!

Revisited this place a couple of times and will recommend to my friends.
Excellent food and a very friendly and cheerful host that gave good recommendations. Very unique take on Thai food as well.
Eating here on a weekday lunch is really peaceful. Enjoyed their set lunch alot.
I love Nepalis food. I love the herbs taste

One of the best lok lok I ever have, the original sauce that came with it is already very nice as it is, and they still provide option for extra sauces!

Appreciate Daniel and Meng for going extra mile, making the delivery this evening when there's no grab driver. Thank you!
Dinner for 3... Hotplate tofu was good, sauce is different from the usual. Prawn paste chicken was tasty! The salted veg duck soup serving was generous. Orh Nee was a let down. Wasn‚Äôt fragrant...
Came down here for some HengHwa cuisine, ahhh‚Ä¶ never disappoint! Gotta make reservation if you are coming down during dinner time. Will come back!
Authentic Indian food.Great service. Mutton must try
Big portion, im soooo amaze, very quick serving with great food
Great location, easily access through public transit. Food is delicious and portion is big, esp given the price u have to pay. Highly recommended!

If you‚Äôre looking for a simple, honest Japanese style cuisine, and you‚Äôre nearby, Tamako is a no brainer.

You get this feeling that families frequent this place, which says a lot about the affordability and accessibility of the food. We ordered a don, and various side dishes; I recommend the home made potato salad and the croquette.

The oyako don we had was sumptuous and filling; the egg was both runny and had texture at the same time.
Good beef mala and sour fish. Super addictive and appropriate for cooling evening. Spice level can be adjusted to suit your tastebuds. Overall a good experience.
Nice üê† and üê£ very economical price
Komala‚Äôs is one of the most excellent Indian food restaurants in Singapore. To try vegetarian Indian food, you must visit Komala‚Äôs! Highly recommended!

Decent food at affordable prices in Novena!
Should expect huge lunch crowd, it‚Äôs a staple for the Novena office workers.

Must Try~ Spicy Pork Noodles (dry): the noodles texture is amazing, cooked to perfection. Sauce is flavourful, abit too savoury with a hint of spice. Pork is succulent and flavourful as well.
Pan Fried Buns: It‚Äôs like Xiao long bau combined with a fried bun. The bun contains flavourful soup with a crispy bottom.

This is family members business different people have their own way of Charging the food price. I have been there many times same items l have but different prices Either the brothers and sisters charging you. Food l consider good. Beef rendang average ok ok
Food was good. Ambience was ok. Accessible as there is a bustop just outside the place. Must try the chicken cutlet rice. My fav in the menu so far.
In a time where burger shops are getting ahead of themselves, trying to be gourmet and all, good old McDonald‚Äôs is the best. Honest for what it is. The taste of no pretence is most delicious

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: Really love shopping here plus the customer service is really nice ! The chicken essence is really convenient for a mother like me who needs the extra boost!

I ordered prawn paste chicken, sliced fish hor fun, cereal prawns, ngoh hiang and spinach with 3 eggs which came to a reasonable $65. All were S except for the hor fun which was L. I've eaten here a few times and the quality was as good as ever. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is the ambience which is pretty basic and the noise level could be high during peak meal times.

One of the highly recommended Vegetarian restaurant in SG!!!
Nice food with affordable price. Remember to make reservations in advance to avoid from long queuing.
Petai was one of the best i ever try cooked in vegetarian way. Their hor fun is quite special too in crispy fried hor fun.üëçüëçüëç

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Went there with family on 15 Sept for mookata. Food is not bad as usual though the ventilation there is slightly poor. I would recommend you to wear your most unpopular clothes there.
Special shout out to cheese bacon wraps, smoke duck , pork belly and basically all e meat haha.

The ice cream will be a good ending after dinner. Self service and you can grab a huge portion for urself. Additional to mention that the service stuff is amazing. Friendly and helpful. Feels like you are dining in Bangkok.
Chicken and mutton dhum biriyani are very delicious. Daalcha is very tasty. It concur my taste buds on each time.

Good food and great price. Can't go wrong with their typical Malay delicacies like mee rebus, soto and satay. You'll burp louder when you try their specialties which they offer. Go try it out. You won't be disappointed...
