restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Decent food; but a little pricey for the seafood. Like the Fried oyster, braised duck with tofu (tofu is really tasty), sea cucumber and cold crab. However, the server is a little pushy on the order - keep telling you to order the lobsters, goose, some special fish etc. Be wary, a single order of lobster can be 300++ after 50% discount, crab is about a 100 etc

Fish head steamboat here is the best i‚Äôve had so far. Every dish is savoury and awesome. Cold crab was just normal not fantastic. left out of the pictures is this cai po kwai teow that , i kid you not, the best i‚Äôve had in my life so far. really awesome!! Definitely order the kwai teow. No regrets. Fish head steamboat is a cut above all the other steamboats i‚Äôve ever had. $65 for a small one. It was enough to go around for my mum, wifey and me. Generous Fresh tasty fish slices and they constantly refill the super savoury soup! i signed up for the member and got a instant 20% disc on the steamboat. We also had yam paste for dessert (pumpkin and ginkgo options available) Service was excellent, generous refill of soups, tea. was there on a weekday evening and was not crowded. I would definitely visit again and strongly recommend to anyone looking for a hearty, satisfying chinese cuisine meal . :)

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Quite simply, amongst the best chicken rice I've ever eaten. And the char siew and roast pork is sublime too. Don't let the naysayers put you off!  The crowds of regular customers is testimony to the quality of the food.

ordered a foodpanda self-pick up order. when i arrived i ask the staff at the pickup area if the food is ready. he rudely told me just go and wait and dont ask? waited a good 20-30mins past the stipulated pickup time. when i asked him again he shouted at me to go ask the stall itself why is the food not ready?! attitude problem

Food is good, and has a lot of variety to choose from, you can also pick the Lok Lok you want and ask the staff to fry for you. The staff are nice too. And they have this chicken satay it's very very nice will recommend. The bad thing is about the clip that you clip on for the fried Lok Lok is a bit dirty... Overall good place to eat. And they have a 20% discount when you like and share the page and one of their post

[Promotion] Love their steamed Thai fish promo! Entire fish (both sides!!!!!) for only $12.90. Cant get a better than this. Also, you get to choose from a list of flavours like Thai style, clear tomyum, red tomyum, lemongrass.... great value for money!
Regular hangout. Authentic Japanese restaurant. Favourite rice bowl. Friendly staffs. Price a little on the high side. But will still go back for the good food. üòÄ
The food was really good.
Best roast duck at northpoint branch
Love the authentic flavours of Indian vegetarian delights. The set meal makes for a pretty hearty meal leaving me satisfied and wanting to come back to sample the other palatable-looking selections.
Value for money lunch sets with great quality!
I went this place on holidays time.so many crowd there.i bought my dinner food.seating is not more.i think 30 peoples can sit and eat there.taste good.thank u
Overall its good for a normal western stall
Feels like home cooked kind of food . The variety of congee is a dream . They have cheesy popcorn chicken congee to the favourite century egg congee. I chose claypot chicken today .

My family has been coming to this restaurant for more than 10 years. This evening was the first time we had a very disappointing dinner. Quality of food has dropped a lot. Even hot tea wasn't hot. May not go back again.

Here is my honest review useful to you:
I visited for the first time with much apprehension. I read the recent reviews of this place, and was quite afraid that the bad reviews were true. I felt uncertain but decided to take the risk at the end.

I booked in advance for a table, and I pre-ordered the famous Sheng Jian Bao (basically Xiao Long Bao but fried).

I entered the shop to a welcoming boss. Seated, and looked at the menu. The menu is very limited especially for a China mainland-hailing restaurant. These types useually have very large menus.

This is my opinion regarding the limited menu. I actually like it because it tends towards quality dining, fine dining. What do I mean? Simple, the harder it is to make dishes, the more effort it takes, the smaller the menu offered by the chef. Commonsense. So, I hope none of you ugly customers criticise them for this point. Menu is limited, but so what? Every dish is lovingly made. Many dishes are handmade.

I ordered quite a number of different dishes. Probably about 25% of the entire menu.

Here is my general comment on the food. How was it? Excellent. Excellent. Excellent. The noodles were handmade, and no, I am not just telling you it is handmade just because the menu says so. I can see and taste that the noodles are handmade. The shape, the non-uniformness, the springiness, the body, the texture. Handmade noodles.

The vegetables were cooked simply in fragrant oil. Excellent. Definitely novel to the usual "HK Kai Lan" or "Spinach in Oyster Sauce" in zichar stalls/chinese restaurants.

The Xiao Long Bao was good enough to rival Din Tai Fung.

But the main star of the show was the Sheng Jian Bao. I will not go into detail. All I will say is that it had taste and bite to it. It isn't just xiao long bao wrapped in a different-shaped bao. It is more than that. A Bao in its own right.

The red bean bun dessert was a very good finisher to an excellent chinese meal. Sweet but not too sweet. Very chewy bun.

I may not have described every dish to you, but I want to end off by telling you that from what I have tried, I can tell that this is a quality over quantity place.

Some commentators complain that the portions are too small. I say this: the prices are small too. Definitely cheaper than eating dim sum in expensive hotel chinese restaurants. If you think the portion is small, order more than 1 serving. Very simple. Very, very simple. There is quality in their dishes. Handmade noodles and handmade baos require a lot of labour effort, labour hours. You think they buy their Bao skin from a distributor then wrap meat inside? Of course they have to knead the dough, flatten it, cut it into small circles, and wrap meat and veg inside. Wake up, Singaporeans. You expect to pay cheaply for a lot of Baos?

Some commentators complain that the service is slow. I say this: it is run by a very slim crew. Their food is quality. You expect crazy, big-chain, 20-man kitchen to churn out your food? The consolation is that they serve your dishes once or twice every 10mins. So it is actually okay. It takes a long while for every dish to come out, but at least it keeps coming. They dont do one table by one table from what I observed.

Some commentators complain that the boss shows favouritism. I say this: You dont? I thought most of you are chinese too? "Ka Ki Lang"? "Guan Xi"?  So what if the boss likes to chat with regulars, and laughs with them? So what?

Finally, they serve free flow chrysanthemum tea. You can see the yellow flower petals in the jar served to you.

Amazing. Yes, the best chinese restaurant I have gone to. I think of the expensive, grand chinese restaurants.... you know what? They're different. Hard to compare. But this place doesnt lose out on taste at all. Not at all.

I wish them the best. I can tell they just want a humble, simple, quite life in this AMK enclave.

As for you, make sure you call well in advance to book your table and your Sheng Jian Bao. Simple. Ignore all the rubbish comments here from ugly Singaporeans. Call, book, then, go, and eat. Very simple.
Did not order any food from them but I've ordered in the past and food is not too bad either. Their service quite fast. Not bad.

Have been patronising Loklok 1991 for quite sometime and I must say that their Loklok standard is one of the more consistent ones out there. This stall is mend by young hawkers and have been around the area for a few years now. The coffeeshop has a few other stall that sells very nice food such as curry chicken and Thai food, including mookata as well as western cuisine.

Back to the Loklok review. Comparing it to the ones that I have tried before elsewhere, it is one of my favourite. From the sauce that they use, the chilli options that they have and the freshness of the food, it has been great so far. Their choices of Loklok is also quite wide but so come early or you might not be able to get some of the favourite options such as mushrooms, brocoli and etc.

Keep up the consistency and I will visit everytime I want to bring my friends over for supper!
Food was average, Chinese pancake and pan fried dumplings was the best on the menu. Its worth a try if u are in the area but its not a place you would go out of your way for.
Unfortunately it was not opened on a Fri... So.... üò≠üò≠
My second time back here. Affordable tze char and fish head hotpot in the heart of CBD. Got the teochew in my excited.

Always good value with delicious food at super reasonable prices.
The bbq ribs were so yummy !! Will definitely return soon !!

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Environment not bad but food abit pricey..
I ordered ala carte instead of buffer style.. cashier should attach the order form with the receipt together so that we can tally with what we ordered..

Service is not good, just walked in the restaurant like a self-service place. Weren‚Äôt interested in having us as customers. Food takes forever to come. Over an hour wait is unacceptable. The restaurant wasn‚Äôt even full. Pricing is also on the high side.

Only good things are the atmosphere and taste was alright, we just hope their service and wait time can be improved soon.

Update: Still waiting over an hour, repeated check-in with staff but nobody gave us an answer.
First visit to Ichiban Sushi @Ang Mo Kio... good service from floor manager and food is fresh and tasty...
At $1/stick, nice loklok (and sauces) made from fresh ingredients, together with good service, we'll definitely be back again!

Very old school restaurant. Came here for the first time with fres. Reminds of fragrant garden in Upper Serangoon and chin lee in bedok. Overall dishes were OK, in particular the chicken was well roasted.

The food is delicious and nice, reasonable price. You Should try their assam fish head. really nice! however the place is not near any mrt, the fastest way is to take a grab or take bus no. 23 from Boon keng Mrt and alight before expressway if you are not driving.

Love this place. Great for team bonding, family bonding or just a fun gathering with friends. Love the concept, affordable pricing, and best of all, no cleaning after cooking. Will definitely be back.

Disappointing food standards and overpriced.  Oyster Omelette is just fried egg and canned oysters placed on top of it, definitely not the way it is cooked in Thailand.  Basil Leaves Pork with rice and egg, another dish that is not cooked Thai style i.e. has carrots and other veg mixed into it that ruined the taste, and very overpriced. Fried Kai Lan using kai lan that is many days old, not fresh, tasteless and overpriced dish.  Not recommended at all.

24 hours teochew cuisine and cantonese handmade timsum. Nice ambience, friendly staff and good food at reasonable price. Located next to lor 8 Toa Payoh Market n Food centre.
10pm to 10am 20% discount.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Have a good meals... The meals are tasty.. Specially their mutton dum briyani so good... And the staffs so friendly...

Pricey but delicious food.

Eat first pay later, no receipt. not sure if the price is as per menu.

I ordered chicken set ( briyani chicken) does not look like wall picture...seem like missing side dishes.

My friend ordered ala carte 2 meats and 1 veg no carb that came out to be $10.

Located near the original section of Northpoint Shopping Centre.
Best to avoid meal times to skip the crowd.
Wide variety of Japanese food selection, from sashimi, sushi, don and noodles.
Prices were still considered reasonable.
Services rendered was very basic. Nothing outstanding or worth mentioning about their services.
Maybe because, all the orders could be placed through the iPad, so minimal contact with the staffs.
Still one of the classical places to go for sushi in Singapore.

Had a great lunch with my husband and celebrated his birthday there. The environment was peaceful as there's a few people at that time. The foods were good and the portion was enough for 2 pax.  I wanted their baked oyster coriander but sadly, it was unavailable. They gave us complimentary chicken wings and cakes. It was sweet of the staffs and customers there to sing birthday song for my husband haha. The malay supervisor was friendly but the other staffs were a bit quiet. It would be a perfect 5 stars if they had ask if i finish my plates before giving the cake because i still had some food left.

Celebrated Father‚Äôs Day here. Coming here to try the food because it‚Äôs recommended by danielfooddiary. The food is fantastic. We tried the otah bread, ice latte, croffle chicken & seafood pasta. Price wise is $20 ish per pax. Ambience is good too.

Had a wonderful experience dining at Tanoke for Nespresso Restaurant week! Food was delicious (special appetisers only available for restaurant week) and the service was impeccable. The servers were attentive and patient in explaining the menu to us. Will definitely come back!
Nice setup with individual grill for each person. Do be prepared to wait for a table and allocations of tables will run out. Love the array of sauces that can accompany your meats.
Reasonably priced n all dishes ordered were very tasty.
Food taste gd

New menu and WOW - it's great. The 3 fish appetiser is amazing, new fish donburi sets are great. I liked this place before but it was getting a bit boring... However, now it's like an old good place that just got refreshing and better. Well done!!!
typical malay nasi padang stall. must try the rendang but the price is a bit expensive.
A nice and homey little restaurant. Food here is delicious but sadly some or the item on the menu is perpetually unavailable. Will be back again if we are in the neighborhood

Ordered delivery with small little hiccup but was very quickly and efficiently resolved by manager Vincent (hope i remember his name correctly) Food delivered on time and was very nice and fresh. Especially for the pork Tonkatsu although not as crispy but at least is not soggy at all. Salmon is fresh too. All the foodie were delicious and yummy thank you!
Great fun

Very friendly staff, nice variety of mainland Chinese dishes, including Sichuanese, Hunanese and dongbei food.  Not earth shattering, but generous portions, good value and very comforting.  (And open until midnight!)

It‚Äôs a amazing ice cream
Taste good . Must tryüëç

Visited this place for North Chinese food. Very clean.
I had the Jia Zhiang Mian and Steamed Vegetarian dumplings. ‚Ä¶

Nice Western food for the price at a restaurant, has promotions for lunch but went there for dinner so it was quiet and not so crowded, suitable for small group gatherings and family, kids get apple juice when they order from the kids menu.

Spacious and good lighting, water is self serve and you can pick either hot or cold water from the dispenser.

Ordered the chicken baked rice while my friend picked the steak. Her steak was juicy and the doneness was medium just as she requested. I enjoyed the cheesy chicken bake rice, as I find the rice fragrant and the cheese went well with it.

Desserts wise they have a couple of interesting choices, drinks as well but we were rushing off elsewhere so if you have time and just want to chill at the restaurant you could order dessert and drinks to share.

Service staff were friendly and nice. Overall a pleasant experience. The food is homely and will visit again.
The food is decent
Don Tai Fung is a goto for good dim sum and other delicious Chinese food. The service is always quick, but the line up to get in can be long. Don't let that turn you away, the food is worth the wait.
No regrets with the claypot chicken. Flavourful and generous serving of braised chicken. Nuggets of salted fish also found in the rice. Yum. Though I wish for more lap cheong every time.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: The waitress very helpful and friendly! Good nice üëç

A shout out to Stephanie! Not only did she show empathy towards me but also her impeccable service!

Upon seeing me with hands full of stuff today, she rushed up to me and helped me w my bags before ushering me to the cashier for my takeaways! She's so thoughtful even towards the end of service that she took a big pc plastic bag for me to put all my stuff in! I was literally blown away  and touched by her thoughtfulness, empathy and wonderful service!

Hope the organisation will have more staff like her as it's hard to come by nowadays.

Thank you Stephanie and keep up the good work ! Hope to see you soon again üòÅ

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: This is a very busy outlet but you can be guaranteed of consistently good chicken rice that is so fragrant and chicken that melts in your mouth. The fish head curry comes recommended and I like the freshness that tasted directly from the sea. The supreme pork chops and prawn roll are tasty.  Recommended to make reservations if coming in large groups.

Simple Zai Char Chinese cuisine restaurant
First time visiting, ordered stir-fried ginger & spring onion beef, broccoli with mushrooms, bitter-ground melon soup.
Soup was good & tasty..
Never  miss  roti  prata  extra  mutton  curry,  you  must  try  it.
No kidding.. this is really really good.. and to think that I've been here for the lor mee all this while really triggers me! The Penang Prawn Noodles is da bomb!

We have found this place by chance while strolling around Blaestier Road. Since then we never stopped going back. The food is delicious and the owners are a lovely couple that make you feel at home. Cannot recommend this place enough!! üòç

Been here with my family weekly since they opened as I stay nearby and glad to say we are still as satisfied as the first time we are here! Food always good. We always order their beehoon and meesua and recently they added some items to their menu and their crabs promotion is very worth it and super tasty! I must say taste even better than some of the high rated seafood restaurant's crab. My mum loves their red wine chicken and my children loves their Ëæ£Â≠êÈ∏°! Will be back this weekend with my family! üëçüèªüôÇ

First and last visit. Absolutely disgusting rude staff that will continuously rush you to place your orders.
Food was average and the ventilation sucks big time so you leave smelling like a kitchen.
Doesn't warrant a second visit at all.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Food there was delicious but a little salty to my preference. Tried to order take away frozen dim sum from them for breakfast for my family but seems like is still the best to eat there as the frozen dim sum which we ordered wasn‚Äôt as good.  Their best dish is giant har gow and lotus rice

Japanese styled restaurant provides good value food for family, kids menu available which they would love to order. Good for group gathering or by ownself to seat by sushi train table. May have to queue  to be seated during peak hours.
This hawker stall has ceased operating.

A very traditional looking shop and my friend commented she felt like shes back home in China. The Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâwas really good. Not overly seasoned and jus right with rice. Love the salted chicken, simple but yet can taste the original taste of the dish. The chilli is really good as some reviewers have commented. ÁÆóÁõòÂ≠êis very unique.. unlike the commercial selling ones that's very chewy, this is slightly more towards sour and also very powdery full of yummy yam rather than flour.

One of the best, if not THE BEST Penang Lor mee I have ever eaten. ( My photo doesn't do justice to it!)

Mouth- 'Full' of taste with thick gravy that seems to coat each strain of noodles! The chilli isn't over powering, subtly spice up the taste, simply making it perfect.
I had issue ordering online and the owner is so kind to look into for me.
My craving fulfilled! You should have yours too!

Staff -
Staff were attentive and kind, quick to respond and aware of our needs.

Food -
To be honest, the food was not great. We ordered the Zuwai Chanwanmushi, Salmon Aburi roll and Kani Mentai Mayo Roll. We much prefer Itacho Sushi‚Äôs rolls.
More affordable, and tasty.

Environment -
The environment was chill, but it was busy as it was on a Sunday night, we waited 15 minutes to be called for our turn.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Is nice but not excellent at $6.20 per plate.  They could have given more sambal chilli to serve with the rice.
Unable to use the "deals" from the mcdonald app but overall serving speed was relatively quick.
The food here is really delicious, especially the claypot rice and crab rassam. The owner is extremely friendly too, and treated us a complimentary side dish for CNY. Highly recommended!
Taste of food alright, just that sometime rather clamp.. especially pre-covid

Hidden gem in an unassuming coffeeshop.

I had the Kurobuta Toroniku Ramen and Takoyaki. Portions were good and soup flavour was *chef's kiss*, not too overly salty (which is what you would usually find in other ramen stores) but at the same time very flavourful. The star of the ramen was definitely the meat, it melts in your mouth!

Will definitely be back again for more üòã

Taste is not bad, normal price. I personally like this kind of train conveyor belt üò¨. We came for weekend dinner, a lot of empty tables. Just that we needed to queue for a while because they took quite some time to assign tables..
There were many options available. My personal favourite was the bbq.
Good place to eating.....enjoy

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Had my birthday dinner here, Nothing to complain about
Quality of food is top notch, chef‚Äôs culinary skills is undoubtedly good
Service is super fast and pretty good, I mean like really fast.
Price is very competitive for the quality and environment, as proven by the full seating.
had the broiled chicken, stir fried mee sua, braised duck, lobster porridge (whole lobster), vege, salted egg yolk prawn with tea- only 55pp after tax

Will definitely come back again!

Tried their Smoked Duck Ramen & Garlic Ramen, and I took the Garlic Ramen. For someone who prefers a stronger taste, this garlic is on the lite spectrum.

Overall, the soup base is still tasty. One thing to note is that the service crew here is friendly and provide prompt service. This is also a halal restaurant that‚Äôs suitable for our Muslim community.
Indian/Malay food stall. Still one of the better stalls serving reasonable food. Prata is good.

Chope voucher brought me here! Voucher for $21.80 - UP $28.80 - 5 kinds of sashimi, 3 pieces each! It was really nice and fresh.

Had a bowl of ramen (not shown which is the kakiage) which was a nice and comforting meal for a rainy day.

Didn‚Äôt know of this lovely place but thankful I made a trip here :)

Kudos to the young lady who served us, she was so sweet and patient. Great service!

Will be back here again!

My go-to place whenever I need a quick fix of Malaysia taste. The taste of the Char Kway Teow is consistent but they do not allow any customisation üòÖ

I would recommend the Nasi Lemak, Mee Hoon Kueh, Claypot Bak Kut Teh & Claypot Rice!

The Cendol is the best that I have tasted so far. Very fragrant gula melaka taste üòã

The only thing i can say about the restaurant
That can be improved is the seating,because it was somewhat cramped for me and my family, other than that food was good and portion size..., well the photos explain itüòä

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Food was amazing. Of all the Indian Foods that I have tasted so far, this one stand out to me as "best in class". Sheer quality of the food is impeccable and beyond comparison. I strongly recommend and will continue to recommend to my family and friends. If you have not tasted yet, try it and you won't regret. Thanks and its simply the best.

We ordered the Teochew and Tom yum broths and they were delicious. 4 pax shared 2 broths and it was actually quite okay, cos the pots though advertised as individual pots, were a good size. They allowed us to add soup later on. All the ingredients we ordered were very fresh. The fish ball with fish roe was especially delicious. What a good satisfying meal.
Price is reasonable. Food is tasty & many varieties available.

(Translated by Google) good to eat.

(Original)
Â•ΩÂêÉ„ÄÇ

Like the jab foodcourt style and the food is good :)

Student price at $5.90 is affordable too for students. Else is slightly costly for a meal with no veg
Good portion of chicken cutlet, fries and coleslaw. Worth the $6.

Had prata, Briyani & Thosai. All were very good. Even the lime juice was well made (not too sour nor sweet). Ambience is good with distancing measures in place. Will definitely be back here again üëçüèª

Nice casual and informal atmosphere, wide varieties of Indian food. The service is friendly and food served very fast. The lamb shank biryani is nice and good price. Prata, thosai, teh halia, milo donasaur are all very nice. Can be crowded sometimes inside the restaurant. Some prefer to dine in the five footway which is more casual  and relaxing. Good hangout place amongst the locals who need a nice Indian food fix.

A China Chinese staff asked my pregnant wife to bring a baby chair and place it by herself. I got speechless about this rubbish service. Food is nothing special but price is too high considering poor service and lack of hygienic. It it interesting that this type of food stall still can survive. I will never come here again for the rest of my life.
Very tasty dishes and good presentation with visual effects . Please keep up the good work üôèüëçüëèüèª

Nicely lit stall with an even nicer uncle recommending me what to order. Ordered the ribeye. Food came fast and presentation was good compared to typical hawker western. Taste very good for the price you pay. Will be back to try others.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Very authentic food, taste is really good, among the best Chinese food I had in Singapore. For someone who is tired of crowd & popular business place, long queue, noisy environment, restaurant chain with same taste everywhere you go, this is a perfect option. Away from main business, a quiet & peace hidden gem near Newton MRT & Newton food center.

Very nice atmosphere with friendly service, provided separate wipes for cleaning utensils and hands, also provided welcome tea before the meal & Ginseng Oolong tea after meal to clean the taste from mouth.

Meat is well cooked and tasty, vegetable is fresh; fried rice is really large portion that allows 4 people to share. Tea is nice too, good quality Chinese tea with extremely good value, $3 for a whole pot. Waitress is very helpful in providing suggestions, service is always on time.

I would definitely recommend this place, and will come back again.
Love their steak
Nice, well-managed outlet with good food and drinks which are promptly prepared and served.

Just went on a sunday evening with my family of 5. We ordered 2 plain naan and 1 garlic naan, one poori set, one butter chicken, one tofu sambal among a few other things. The naans came first and it was 1 butter naan and 2 garlic naan. As it was quite busy we just let it go but after most of the other food arrived, the butter chicken for the naan still havnt arrived and whatever naans that were left (we started eating cos we were so hungry) was turning cold and hard! It was after 3 to 4 times we asked them to check on our butter chicken that it finally came, a measly 3 piece in a less than 10 cm diameter flat dish! Service was atrocious but we understand it could be due to busy crowd but at least be apologetic and learn to serve the curry and butter chicken first before the naans, otherwise, how do we eat it plain without them?? Plus, the naans have turned cold and hard by then! Not to say the dishes were priced 10$ and above for a pathetic portion and tastes were also all salty! We will never patronise this place again! Only patronise this place if you enjoy lousy service, high pricing for ridiculously small portion and awful tasting food!

Most Thai restaurants in Singapore are either 1- fancy and pricey 2- down and dirty or 3- cooked for non Thais so not authentic. A-Roy Thai is different. It is just like the Thai food you would get in Thailand. That's because it's run by a family from Udon Thani who bring the chef in from their home town and keep the food real. The Isaan dishes are best but the dishes from throughout the country are all pretty good. A family member is usually there (ask for Chayut). Beers are cold. Service is fast. Please enjoy the best Thai food in Singapore

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Very bad experience at this outlet on a sunday night, nearly empty. Food was decent but service by this older chinese? auntie waitress, Jov was hideous. Jov was very rude and constantly staring down at us close to us from the corner. The restaurant was empty, Jov. We can see you.
When we flagged her down asking for refill or utensils, she repeatedly exclaimed shes busy. The restaurant was almost empty, about 20% full.
My previous review was longer and got removed, but my experience stands. This waitress Jov has a bad attitude.
very friendly staff! and food is yummy

Food was decent. But in the middle after serving second or third dish, the food stopped coming for about 30minutes and children were left hungry and we were left waiting there for a long time when only half-done with lunch. In the end, we were told 2 of the dishes were OOS and we had to cancel.
friendly boss and staff, food really good!!
The begedil and chilli was good. The rice was a bit hard for my liking and the chicken could have been seasoned longer.
Excellent foods. Good service. Average ambient for the price.

Pros: Prices are okay but by no means cheap.
Cons: Quality is average, the salmon I ordered was burnt. The service and waiting time were terrible. I waited 30 mins for just one salmon don and they asked me for my order 3 times.

My go-to heartland pasta shop! Love both their cream and aglio olio varieties.

Became a regular after ordering via food delivery apps during Covid period. Unfortunately delivery is no longer available, but it is worth a walk over once in a while.

Unpretentious and good Japanese food located in a quaint estate along Upper Thomson road.

I've exclusively ordered the katsu-don here many times and have always been satisfied by it. The flavor reminds me of what I used to have about 10 years ago as a kid which I distinctly remember the taste of but could never find it again until here (cue the ratatouille flashback scene). The tender tonkatsu soaked through with delicious dashi stock and the egg cooked just to the right doneness to coat every mouthful of rice with egg and dashi sauce.

What you'll expect here is homely, good food with no fuss at a reasonable price tag. I cannot recommend it enough.

Putien (Northpoint City)
The food are serve very well, not too greasy nor bland. Absolutely the taste of Putien. Environment are suitable for family or friend to gathering. The waiters all serving us very well, they will keep on changing the dish for us to make sure we have a good experience to enjoy the food. It really feel like a VIP when we enter to the restaurant. Definitely will come back again
Good value. Lobster and sharks fin on promo is of decent size. Taste wise not the best but better than many mid range restaurants.

My first attempt lunch experience.

Personally, I like their main menu items, the savoury items are not to my liking.

Overall dining experience is good. Nice place and ambient.

fried rice a little bland.
but overall, ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖis good, xlb is decent (skin on the thicker end)
Their chicken nanban don (fried chicken with tartar sauce) was delicious.. Service was quick and fuss free as well on a Sat lunch
gv a try lads

First time here for their dim sum, and really enjoyed our meal. The staff are very welcoming and attentive, and food was really good too! Highly recommend ordering the flaky egg tarts and dumplings in spicy vinegar. The liu sa pau was also great (note that the bun is in crumbly pastry form, not soft bread pau). Will definitely return!
Were here for Chinese New Year Reunion Dinner, the service is good and prompt. The best dish is the Noodles, it is so good i had 2 servings !

To be honest, the soup base is on the sweet side, even with the side of chilli, it was more to the sweet rather than spicy. I prefer savory taste so might not try again but other than that, the food is fresh. I would recommend their satay instead.

Tried it on it opening day. Not bad at all!  Will come back to visit soon.

Walau...came back 9months later and tried their oyakodon.. the rice is watery fully soak in soya sauce...
Good place to eat. Affordable price for one portion.

A new tenant at Safra Jurong. Prata portion is reasonable & cripsy. Unlike some other prata whereby thickness is very thin, I prefer Spingleaf prata thickness which is just nice. Dipping their prata into the thick & luscious(tomato tinch) complete the ultimate oomph to my eating pleasure.

Takeaway order during weekend morning peak hour(with grab & in store order)  is unexpected fast around 7 mins. Highly recommended for future prata visit :)

Updated review: Do show your Safra membership card upon payment for 10% discount off as Springleaf Prata Safra Jurong staff will not provide discount automatically.

Updated Aug 2018.
Standard drop from 4 to 2 stars. Mee Goreng is almost ketchup noodle

5 stars for the wonderful dinning experience and friend, attentive staff. The food were well prepare and presentation. I must say my family were impressed by the quality and portion! The portion was generous. The deco of the restaurent was very well design to give a relaxing mood. It provide a very pleasant dinning experience, my family like it, we will certainly back again. Well done!

Ordered ÁÉ§‰∏≤- chicken and pork belly, quite nice, min order of 5 pcs, after eating the 1st 5 pc I ordered 5 more pcs.
Also ordered the ÈÜãÊ∫úÁôΩËèú. It‚Äôs quite expensive for veg and the plate is quite small too. Taste is ok, for those who don‚Äôt like too spicy and sour dish shd be ok. But I like my ÈÜãÊ∫úÁôΩËèú to be more spicy.
Overall taste is good for the dishes I ordered. Will come back and try other dishes next time.
Others ppl wrong order serve to us.. terrible.. food is cold too!!!

Service at this place is like a unicorn - absolutely non-existent.
There were occasions of real confusion when we were conversing, obviously, in the same language but nothing went across.

this is 1 star because that is the minimum Google requires.
Very good service, food was very good too. Surprise food gem at ITE College Central.
Ordered their prata which was pre-cooked and stored in a container, naturally prata was cold and soggy. Price on the more expensive side. Wouldn't go again

Made famous by an exposure on TV. Their culinary skills are not too bad and  the family had served the neighbours over the decade if not more. Prices are fair and there are ample parking. But prepare to wait on weekend dinners.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Crabs overcooked, kailan bitter. Worse is the crazy irritating techno music blasting throughout. It's supposed to be a relaxing experience by the river - but the music is really irritating.
Good ambiance and good food. But there is lots of room for improvement on service and timing of food serving.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Jjampong was delicious but a tad too spicy for me.  The spicy fried chicken taste ($35!) was good but the batter was a little too soggy for my liking.

This is our first visit, u need to be extremely patient when ordering ala carte buffet. Food portion was nice and small(i.e. 2 person gets 2 piece of prawn and so on) so no wastage. However U have to wait for like 1-1.5 hr for the food to be served. I don't know if it's a norm at this restaurant but seriously we were there from 11:30 til 2:30, some dishes we ordered st 12 noon just got served at 2:10 just now and we told them we are full and it got served too late so they took them back to the kitchen.
With the bill add up to about $190 for 4 adults I think next time we'll just go to Silk restaurant instead.
Great crispy chicken cutlet with good portion for money. If you are alright with waiting at least 10 minutes for really good coffeeshop western food then you should, nay, MUST try this.

Pros: nett price
Cons:
We went there Sunday night, 19th September 2021, and there wasn't a lot of people but it was very chaotic. The staff were arguing (guy in yellow shirt at counter was screaming to the staff to "open their eyes") and there was a lot of banging of plates. It's a small indoor seating area so the noise was very hard to ignore.
We ordered a set meal with one mushroom soup(top up $1, the soup of the day was chicken soup) and one chicken soup and chocolate cake.
My friend is a vegetarian so ordered veggie chow mien and the mushroom soup. The older lady taking our order didn't write down any of our orders.
We were served two chicken soup and when we informed them, they didn't even realise that we ordered mushroom soup (keyed in wrong order, maybe can write down the order next time?)
The mushroom soup took about 10 minutes to serve.
Then the Chinese waitress served my friend "chicken chow mien" and when my friend asked if its veggie chow mien instead, she was like "oh ya, that"
For dessert, the Chinese waitress served us yellow sponge cake and said it was prune cake and then said it was cheesecake? She didn't even know the menu... It was a regular pound cake (the type you can buy at giant supermarket) and we asked what about the chocolate cake the older lady told us about? And she said they ran out.... They didn't even inform us about it.
Food is edible. But the portion is questionable. Do Not order the pizza. Its $12 for a pan sized, those you can get for better quality for $5 at pizza hut. The dough was also RAW. Also asked for extra sauce because chicken was dry but was told have to add $1 for any sauce lol. This is the first place I've been to where I heard such thing. Other places like Aston don't have?
Overall, horrible service and bad atmosphere. Been here before where we were served by I think it was the owner, older guy with glasses, who was very polite. Unfortunately, this time, was a bust.
Worth for repeated visit.. price below average, quality above average..

This place is worth a visit if you like claypot rice with rice crisps and salted fish. Paired with chilli padi or the chilli sauce provided, it was heavenly. Totally enjoyed the claypot rice. But the other dishes we ordered were nothing to rave about. They were good but not great.

I felt I had gotten poor service.

Asked for chilli for my prata when their menu states chilli $0.6 (I didn't mind sambal or any chilli), they keep saying only got chilli sauce which I say okay.

Then they didn't wanna give, unlikely to return unless their food is so so amazing that I'm ok to tolerate the service standard.

Recommended me to try their crab and said that it is fresh. When the crab is served, the pincer was so watery with little meat like an empty shell. When complaint to lady boss, she just look at it and walk away. The rest of the food there are just normal.
Convenient. Just right at exit 3 at MayFlower MRT. Good Food. üëç

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Menu has wide variety of choices. Food is delicious. This place is open 24 hours. The mutton murtabak is quite delicious.
nice food must tryüëçüëçüëç
Yummy nasi padang, but price can escalate. I had 5 dishes for 13bucks. Some of the stuff can be oily. Eat for an indulgent meal.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Food is good, prata is crispy. But they really have to work on the cleanliness. Table, menu, floor  is always oily. There will always be plates left over. Request to clear but was ask to seat in the shop.

Dined at 3 different Jack's Place over the past month, ordering their signature Fish & Chips. Toa Payoh branch's is most dissapointing, neither the fish nor chips is crispy. Fried potato that is soft is not my cup of tea. Guess the staff in charged of fried food doesnt know the right temperature required.... Fish is fresh though, no fishy smell.

This is the only store that still standing and not changed (except moved stall next to it)
price is ok and service is friendly

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Food is nice, portion is big, boss is friendly, recommended üëç

Portions were way too huge and there was a lot of food wastage :( I wish I had knew beforehand so I could order to share and not waste so much food. Perhaps the place could let people select portion sizes?

Taste wise, not bad - pineapple rice was fragrant, pad Thai had wok hey. The only odd thing was that the Tom Yam soup tasted a little jasmine-y and metallic, which I thought was odd. Sad because I was looking forward to a bowl of nice comforting Tom Yam soup this coooool season.
Made upon order. Very crispy, lovely curry and kopi si kosong!
Good value, but if you‚Äôre looking for something serious this might not be it.

Roasted pork/cha siew rice doesnt come with soup. Beansprout is overly salty and not crunchy enough.  There is something that i cant fathom as well.  My mum asked for dark soya sauce to be placed on the sauce plate but they say they could only pour soya sauce on our plate and not on the sauce plate.  For chilli and light soya sauce,  it is okay to pour into the sauce plate.  When asked the rationale,  they just said it is a rule set by the female boss.  Attitude was slightly rude.

Tried the fried fish with green chilli (ijo?) set.

The fish was well fried and tender. However, the portion was a little bit too small. Taste wise, it was a rather sensational experience!

Worth a try.

I just had my dinner last night and the experience was very disappointing. I ordered a 6 course dinner set at 8pm and the pace in which the dishes were served was so bad, the entire experience was ruined. The first 3 dishes came at 30 to 45 mins interval and the last 3 dishes in a burst because "the kitchen is closing". Toward the end,  my wife had 3 dishes on the table. How is this a fine dining experience?
Fast and efficient, friendly service, good food.

ThevXiso Loong Pows were good...but the skin for Prawn Siew Mai failed in Quality, Taste and presentation.
The skin was just too thick...and spoiled the texture and eating experience!

I went to Hup Kee fishballs noodles a couple of days ago with my wife. I was in the q at 11.10am. After 20 mins, a lady came out and said no more fishballs and taupok. Only left fish cakes. Told her is okay though we were so so disappointed. When it was my turn after 35 mins wait, there were 2 fishballs each in our soup. When we tasted them, it was heaven. I had never ate such a fantastic taste of handmade fishballs. It pays off for our patience. We will definitely go back for his fishballs. Fish cakes were just as good. Noodles were just as great and tasty as well. Ample parking spaces for those who drive.

I am not a fan of porridge but this place cooks up a yummy bowl that I would come back again.

The you tiao was surprisingly still crispy despite been left at counter for a while.

I had the mixed pork porridge which was really a mix of meat, internal organs, pork balls, fried, boiled into a flavourful bowl of porridge.

Wished I had the option white pepper, chives, oil. It was all added before served. Soya bean milk was a little sweeter than I would like.

Food is unique and portions were big, but not mind blowing and price is on the steep side.

Ondeh-Ondeh cake is a crowd favorite with gula melaka bits in between the layers!

Staff are also attentive and polite!

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Price has been up abit. Dinner for 2 pax $33 max full, chicken taste same as most other foods hawker centre. Kang kong very nice but $9 is expensive, sambal very nice. Dumpling soup nothing special to me. Place very warm traditional style, good for family weekend dinning.
Nice ambience cafe. Staff service is good. Ordered the creamy chicken spaghetti. Chicken is salty, noodle creamy yet a bit plain. Maybe will try other food next time.
the food is very good and tasty üëç
First time tried this stall. Ordered lamb chop and was pleasantly surprised by the well marinated meat with rosemary herbs and cooked over fire grill. Best lamb chops so far!

The food standard had dropped so much that this will be my last visit. From the 2 dishes I ordered today, both are NOT Penang food.

I have nearly mistaken the Char Kway Teow as Thai fried pad thai due to the raw beansprouts.

Next come to the Penang Loh Bak, I have to double confirm the dishes name on the menu at the end of my meals. It taste like the ngoh hiang. It also didn't serve with the dipping chilli and loh.

I am not a Mee Rebus fan as yellow noodles is not really my type of noodles. @rahimmuslinfood is the only stall that I am willing to travel all the way from the West to Ang Mo Kio whenever I have craving for Mee Rebus! Their Power Mee Rebus ($4.80) features Cut Chicken and Hard-Boiled Egg drenched with Satay Sauce Topping. The sauce is damn power lor.

Location: Rahim Muslim Food, 453A Ang Mo Kio Ave 10, #01-01, Singapore 560453
Tried the nasi ambeng here. Turned out to be  a grand serving including beef rendang, chicken drumstick, tempeh, veg, steamed rice topped with dessicated coconut. Cooking standard was good.
Food here is tasty and decently priced. Rosti was crispy! Chargrilled chicken was juicy as well. Service was attentive and friendly. Will definitely return. üòä
ordered the pan fried buns and xiao long baos. both dishes arrived very quickly upon ordering but the pan fried buns tasted better. the xiao long baos were quite average.
Been there a few times. Yesterday, as a privilege of the last customer during the day hour. I was given extra fries for free. üòç absolute value for money. Taste of the food is also very nice.
Prata is not oily with nice fish curry. Beehoon soto is good. Tried the mee rebus, as they ran out of soto, taste is average but a bit salty. Wide selection of items though.
Food is great I will come back
Food prices Too expensive
Their normal taste is too plain for my preference.
Semma indeed served a hearty and rich flavourful dishes! It's must to try prawn and mutton satti sooru. Definetly a delightful experience in overall. Me and my family truly enjoyed!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
Crowded on a Friday evening as usual. Lots of diners who did not make reservations had to wait.

Prices were reasonable. Food items were as fresh as can be. Service was good with empty plates cleared regularly.
Loved the idli, dosha and meedu vadai. We ordered these dishes for our small Onam celebration at home. The food made the celebration a pleasant experience for all. Keep up the good work!

A small authentic Shanghai eatery located in an housing estate. It has 7 tables so definitively you need to made an reservations.
If you looking for dumplings, then you will be disappointed as they stop serving due to time constraints.
They have limited items but it is tasty. I would highly recommend Braised Pork Bun. The bun is flavorful, pork is thinly slice and the salted vegetable is slightly sweet and not salty at all. Xiao Long Bao taste is different from others.
Food potion is small so if you are a big eater do order double.

Good value and high bbq quality with meats smoked well! Ordered p1 platter and enjoyed the chicken and pork belly. Sides like the mashed potato were yummy as well. Also special mention for the octopus which I enjoyed, given I'm not a fan of tako. Accompanying sauces made the meats even more yummy. kudos to the friendly boss kelvin :)

Ask for soup for my chicken rice, like which chicken stall rice doesn't provide soup? So i ask this chinese lady which i guess is the "manager" cause her colleagues called her, so i asked that if i could have a bag of soup for my chicken rice. She firmly just said "oh no soup no soup" when i literally saw there is a pot of soup behind them. After i walk off, heard the colleagues together with the manager laugh off at me thinking i didn't hear them. Super disappointed!! Is this how you treat your customer?! RIDICULOUS!!

It serves mainly western food at an affordable price. Previously the steaks came in big portions, but shrunk over the years... more like kids meal nowadays! updated*09/18 price went up again... Chicken cutlet($7.50) portion getting smaller... haiz...

My parents have been bringing me to this restaurant ever since i was a little boy and now i am 28 and they are still bringing me there. Their standard have not dropped once. I will highly recommend this restaurant

Went on Thursday, 130 pm, they have 30% discount daily until 230pm. Then 40% discount from 231pm - 415 pm.

The soups were great, the meats, we ordered beef, pork, fish all tasted good with no funky smell or taste.
Veggies - spinach, mushrooms also were fresh.

You also get a free gelo? (not sure)  dessert
There is an extra price for condiments per person, 2.30sgd
Ate spicy chicken Japchae. Not spicy at all. A bit salty to my taste bud.

Lobster porridge was the highlight; the porridge and the broth was rich and flavorful, but the lobster itself was lackluster at best. Other dishes ordered tasted great too. Overall, it was an enjoyable experience.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Must visit  for yummy scrumptious Traditional South Indian üáÆüá≥ Food! Awesome crispy vadai ! Masala dosa Indian style which tastes like home cooked food! Such a satisfying breakfast ! Deserves the 5 star!  Bru coffee was top of the world !

Dim Sum buffet. They serve pretty fast, keeping coming to the table with offer of different dishes; we don't even need to call for waitress. We end up with 13 dishes + 2 dessert. (We rejected a few other dishes becuz too full). The prawns are fresh,  baos are nice. Only setback is the pork ribs which is abit too salty. The fried red bean + banana pancake was abit too sweet. Worth going back again
bad and rude service with bad food

Great service. Lady waitress/boss very good in recommending and sharing on what‚Äôs available and how to cook.

Although 2 hours time limit they are flexible.  Anyway an hour plus we are all done.

Love their satay and satay sauce. Fried chicken wings taste good as well although everyone goes for Lok Lok. Their herbal soup tastes good. All came out with full stomach and no food wastage.  Free flow ice cream (my youngest ones love it) and soft drinks.

Will return to check out other dishes.

First visit as recommended by a friend. Atmosphere was very cozy and comfortable. Ordered few dishes, fried sea bass and clay pot glass noodle is a must try. Even the Thai milk tea was almost identical to Thailand standard, make me feel like I‚Äôm in Bangkok.
Service was excellent as if you are in the land of Smiles.
Overall this place is strongly recommended.

Apr 2019. I loved the food here. We ordered Kailan, spinach, sambal fish and chicken curry.
Everything was so deliciously done and tasted home-cooked.
Other than the nice food, i saw a harmonious working culture here. The younger Malay staff could speak Mandarin and were respectful to an elderly Chinese auntie.
Lots of positive energy. üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç
Value for money, good fo9d

Coffee Shop pricing and good old school style western food.

Love the potato ball and their coleslaw. The fries are the thick cut type and is nice too (although I love string fries).

The fried rice is very tasty and not overcook.

Love this place.
Market plc‚Ä¶only malay food there.products quality drop‚Ä¶but still acceptable.
Nice cosy Japanese style family restaurant.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Excellent packages, food is very tasty also!
Staff are very friendly. I like the asam laksa noodle soup, the soup are very thick and the curry noodle are tasty. Highly recommend to those missing malaysian food people ü§§üòÅ.

(Translated by Google) delicious

(Original)
ÂæàÂ•ΩÂêÉ

The meat was tender and delicious, the buttered corn as well. Some improvements can be that the coleslaw needs more sauce, and definitely reduce the amount of salt on the curly fries. The fries texture and crispiness was divine!

$1 lok loks are really affordable, flavour is pretty accurate and authentic. Overall solid. But I just wish there were more options like meat skewers and etc. Maybe do a premium $2 per stick series or something. Other than that overall its still a decent hang to get your Lok Lok fix.
Under staff. Only 1 hard working staff at the dining area.. food okay only.
We are regulars here because of the lack of Indian food on campus. The prices are exorbitant and service is poor. As the weeks progress it takes more time to get our food!

Food was a hit or miss depending on the dish you order. My table ordered pork ribs (was quite decent), mushroom truffle pasta (good), teriyaki chicken pizza (meh - the mayonnaise overwhelmed the entire pizza), caesar salad (so-so).

What was not great was the service. One of the waitstaff who is clearly a butch has a really poor attitude and for some reason was just rude to me simply because I was a guy. Could not greet customers properly, and talk decently. My entire dinner was ruined simply because of the way she behaved and spoke. Could tell she was biased because she treated her other butch customers with such kindness and courtesy, but not to others sadly.

NOT RECOMMENDED!
Awesome Lamb shanks here and thier pratas.

Ordered Truffle Beef Set and Bara Chiraisi. The fish were fresh and tasted great! The truffle wasn't overpowering. The searing of the beef was great!! Slightly salty but with the rice, the runny egg yolk, the sauce and top it up with a bit of shichimin made it perfect for me! The portion was generous, too! It was a fulfilling meal!

The drink here was ice yuzu lemon. It was refreshing!

What a gem! Surely will come back here soon! Somemore with 10% cashback with Fave!!

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Enjoy the roti prata here.
Very underwhelming tbh. Ordered chicken basil with egg rice and it was so blend and dry. Probably my last time ordering the same dish here. Might try other dishes the next time though.

Food was worst than I think. Rice were solid is nvm, but hard to chew and you might can swollow with water. The only thing I like is the deco of the table. **If you are not a fan of seafood or hate seafood, MY ADVISE IS NEVER EVER EAT IN THIS RESTRAUNT PLEASE!** It was horrific filled with seafood and I found meatless. Also, the rice I've mention earlier is fried rice, whoch wiol contain eggs, right? NO! Theres no eggs! Everything is meatless! Please for god sake if you hate seafood PLEASE DO NOT COME HERE. That's all.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
This food stall located at the Yishun Park hawker Centre is a pioneer in this dish - the Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang. They combined the traditional Nasi Lemak with one of Indonesia's unique chicken dishes, the Ayam Taliwang.

The chicken for this dish is grilled but the sauce or sambal which makes it truly unique on its own, the Taliwang Sambal. Their rice is absolutely fragrant with coconut milk and the chicken is tender and juicy!

They also have other varieties of Nasi Lemak and also side dishes which you can add-on. All in all, they are an affordable place to get great quality Nasi Lemak!

A pretty awesome place that serves vegetarian food. They have a huge variety of dim sums and also set lunch at decent prices. We order an executive lunch set for 2 pax and order another dish. It was very filling and does not leave a oilly after taste. We will be back again for such to try the other dishes.

I have been eating their Thai food since they were at Clementi! So glad that they have received the recognition that they deserved! Value for money, good portion, delicious, authentic Thai food! Service is good too :) my go to place for good Thai food for sure!

Should have listened to the one star reviews that I saw when queueing, don‚Äôt bother trying honestly. Ate the kimchi stew and it was so sour and the tofu was the cheap yellow circular one that you get from NTUC for hotpot. Even the 7-11 ready to eat kimchi stew for $5.20 was more worth and tastier than this $5 one (that‚Äôs not ready made lol). The rice that came along w it was the star of the show, it was better than the stew and so soft.
Awesome food and ambience! Finally found something decent near my house. Love the tonkatsu and the curry! 5/5 would def come back again.

Often they have offers that make the food affordable. I used to like when they had beer hours that include tasting various beers at a good price. Regular pricing is a bit on a high side considering that their location is in the campus and most students can't enjoy the services. Staff is always friendly however, they tend to force guests to occupy a table they might not necessarily like. As a guest, you need to have a feeling you're welcome. In general, food is alright, however, when you're taking a burger, try to let them know that you want a fresh bun, otherwise you're stuck with the older. I do occasionally go and bring a friend so you might try as well. This will help them improve.
Will return specially for the XO Carrot cake and liu sha bao. The other dim sums are quite average.

Simple yummy home cooked Chinese food done well near Potong Pasir. The place has been around for more than ten years. And one of the best thing, you allow BYOB for wines for $10 corkage. We are definitely coming back here to try other dishes!
Indian and Thaai muslim hotel but idly is not available and dosa also not available in Saturday and Sunday.paratta is special here

Disappointing.

Ordered a drink for takeaway, was asked to wait outside, but took about 25mins to deliver that 1 cup of teh tarik.

Went back in to check, then was told that the drink is left on the table, in a plastic bag carrier.

After clarifying that their cashier already charged me for the plastic cup, I still had to top-up cash for the plastic cup.. staff did not apologize after all that.

The best food court nasi lemak in town, no other place can beat Nasi Lemak Pak Mandor. Pandan rice and sambal are the best ~ I can't describe it well by words, kepak chicken wing had a perfect nice crisp, similarly with the ikan ekor kuning which is very tasty, perkedel or begedil is always tasty as ever.

I would strongly recommend to dine in or if take out, to eat it right away while its warm.

Been their loyal customers since ages and their nasi lemak never disappoint me, always able to maintain the taste.
dis shid SLAPPED

Very odd chirashi don. Are you one that like everything put Into a bowl? A rojak of flavours, texture and ingredients?And I mean, popped rice, chilli, dried shrimp, pickled ginger, turnips, cucumber, flavour rice mixed in with mushroom, a generous serving of wasabi, topped with generous slices of sashimi and a small piece of cake? Yes, sponge cake.

Personally, I prefer my Donburi taste to be cleaner and that I can taste the freshness and sweetness of the fish. In this experience, we weren‚Äôt sure what we were eating. The fish though generous did not taste premium. For $35++ a bowl, a lunch for 2 could send you away $80+ poorer easily. That explain why the restaurant was practically empty.

I don‚Äôt think I will be ever going back. Just too weird and a tad too pricey for donburi for me.
Good Food! Serve in large portion. Worth trying.

went to have dinner on 29 march, was told to sit 1 side of the sofa as usual, food came, and i went over to the other side to take a pic for my sponse and was being told off rudely by the cashier staff i am not allow to even go over to take picture that i will be "fine" for doing so..

come on, its 29 march.. when new Covid safety measure has lighten, i was over for less than 5sec to jus take a picture..

110321 Impromptu TGIT dinner with ‚ù§Ô∏è @ The Larder Cafe, had baked escargots, grilled buttermilk chicken and Black Mama Pork Burger (What a name for a Charcoal Bun burger!)

Osmanthus Latte was somehow a bit of a disappointment with a hint of the flavoured taste, but promptly covered by the heavy coffee flavour, despite being a milk-based latte drink.

Still a good dining place to try out overall !
Expensive drinks
Good food generous potion, friendly cashier aunty. Thank you for the food üôè
Cheap and good economics price for a cheap Japanese meal. Taste is as good as a home cook meal.
Industrial area in AMK for Zi-Char. Their chilli crab was a little spicy though, but nice and very fresh. Well cooked too. Reservations recommended

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content:
I love the place in general, the ambience is nice and cool when I visited that evening. Unfortunately, the music didn't do justice to the place and I had many bites when seated in the open.

The food was average. I liked the Toufu. But not so the fried rice. The squid was OK...

Decent food, but still finding their footing.

Meat noodles are satisfying and portions are generous. The chicken and beans cold dishes are so-so, the dumplings are a bit lacking in soup and meat.

They also ran out of many dishes by the time we went, but to be fair the restaurant was packed full since lunchtime and we only went for dinner.

Hopefully in the future they will have more dim sum varieties!
Delicious cheap green nasi lemak.varieties of add on such as bagedil,chicken wing,fish etc.Do come early to avoid dissapointment.

3.5 stars, friendly and fast service at 12:30 pm, no queue. Soup tasted more like our mixed pork organ Áå™ÊùÇÊ±§ soup than your typical Japanese ramen. The meat has not much fat and is quite hard to bite, overall this will fix your ramen craving.

Food is decent but the service is ridiculously slow.

The customer is often left wondering at the cashier and waiting for the staff to eventually attend to you. Some give up and leave the queue in frustration.

The food preparation time is dismally slow despite the ‚Äúfast food service‚Äù claim by the business. The result is the seating area where few seated diners are actually eating whilst the others are just waiting for their orders to arrive.

My drink order was served at 1042h (took 30 mins!?) and food finally arrived at 1050h (took 40 mins?!)

C‚Äômon guys... get your act together.
Absolutely slow service
Loving the poke bowl I tried today very fresh ingredients are served. üòã Yummy

Very decent Malaysian food can be found here. Yam cake & chee Cheong fun were really good. Nasi lemak was big in portion and allso came with vegetables üëç clean interior and plenty seats. Probably the only downside is that it is less accessible for those not driving.

I really enjoyed this place. The food was great the staff was just so nice. When you have a combination of good food with the excellent service you have a winner. I definitely recommend this place for your next business dinner or a romantic night with you loved one
South Indian food (Veg/Non veg) available in authentic taste in reasonable price. Amenities is good. Can enjoy music when dining..

Decent prata. Both the fish and chicken curry are nice. Briyani is also good.
The queue can get quite long during peak hours. But overall, service is fast.
Although it is not fully air conditioning, it is comfortable eating there. The staffs are friendly n helpful. They will personally served you fried food that just came out from the kitchen.

Brought my family here for the 1st time.  This place definitely deserves a ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è mainly for the pricing and no nonsense good service.

However it failed to get the last star due to its sloppy mushroom soup, garlic bread could have been a bit more toasted.
The saddest part was the steaks were too ‚ÄúChao Tah‚Äù.  Otherwise my steak would have been superb.
My go-to place for Assam Laksa. Love the BKT and Assam laksa better than any shop that served Malaysia food outside. Anyone who misses Malaysia food definitely should drop by for a try.
Great yakitori. Service is fast too.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: My family had a fish head steamboat, la la,veg,crispy noodle all paid for $80+üòÑ
Chill place with beer buckets. Close at 10 tho

One of the the best restaurants that serves home like cooked meals. Initially their cuisine was really spicy and I‚Äôm a person I can‚Äôt take spicy food. After numerous feedbacks, they did actually took it into serious consideration and now I must say they have really improved on their spicy level, and it‚Äôs much more enjoyable to eat! Thank you for considering our feedbacks and allowing different tastebuds and thresholds to really enjoy your food wholeheartedly. I will definitely patronise this shop as this is the only Shop from my understanding does NOT USE MSG in their cooking and their food tastes like a good home cooking. Keep up the good work and kindly keep this level of moderate and mild spicy so everyone one of us can enjoy. üëç

Food that brings us back in time. Tried the chicken chop that is tender and marinated just like we do it at home, old school flavours. The chilled ribeye was correctly done(medium well) tender and juicy, the cost at $13.90, no frills steak at its best. Waiting time approx 15 to 20 mins, very reasonable with the crowds and takeaways.

2person lunch at $88..one platter($16), 2 main dish($22x2), 2 soup($6.90x2 they forget to serve the desert,we also forget there's a desert and we left)...food quality is not bad, price is also acceptable. But next time come after 2.30pm they have 1for1 free main dish.

Hawker stall with really good western food run by a bunch of hainanese folks. We had the chicken chop and pork chop, and they were very well done and tasty!! I would also recommend the fish & chips for its huge portion size.

The fries were crispy, and the garlic bread was delicious too! Very value for money, and top notch quality western food.
$6 for this huge piece of chicken chop

The variety of food here is quite extensive. They serve both India Muslim and Thai Muslim food here. Crowd will start to build up before lunch. This place is quite popular with working adults as well as students from nearby establishments. Place is generally clean and the staff are helpful.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
I give it a 5 star rating as I found 2 stalls were exceptional out of my expectation, although the other 2 with fairly ok taste after my own trial. The soybeam milk and the You Tiao Man are awesome, it's the best I've tried since came to Singapore. The You Tiao Man has no butter flavor, and it's not like the others that it too much stuff, it tastes crisp out side but also light feel inside with a little salty. The boss said there's not so many people make You Tiao in the old way like him, I totally believe.
Astonishingly, the 88 congee was a little disappointed though a lot of people were in the queue. The congee is too thick, rice was not totally melted. Maybe I've tasted too much Cantonese style of congee, I would only give 3 star for this. The Teochew Handmade Pau was ok, I'll give it a 4 star, as it's just doing ok and the same as I tried in a Pau stall in Tiong Bahru. I didn't try the other famous ones like carrot cake, fried fish soap that day as they were not open. But all in all, a place worth to go again!

Yum yum.
Ordered salmon aburi don and unagi roll.
The hakotate mentai was nice!!! (not in the picture)

Tried the green curry chicken, claypot tang hun with prawn, stuffed chicken wings, and Thai fish cake. All pretty good, best amongst these was the tang hun. Nothing stand out for me but all were pretty good. All these for $35.

Ordered food through Deliveroo, food was pipping hot when arrived and it was delicious. Surpassed my expectations for it's pricing. Had to go out of my way to recommend it here. Spring chicken was tender and well seasoned, fries was fried till perfection, beef was tender and coleslaw was super refreshing with chunks of pineapples.
Food is good!

Service is very slow but I can't blame the cook or the waiter. There are only those 2 around juggling the whole tables and online orders. The management is working them unfairly and as result they got scolded by customers quite a lot.

I will agree with the other folks here. This is the best mee soto in Singapore- one that can compare with Indo‚Äôs best. Highly recommended. For the Mee Rubus, they add peanut sauce which is nice but not for those with allergies.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Go on a weekdays to have a three little towers at $43.00++... Weekend will be $48.00 for two little... foods wise are very good Zi cha at a high standard... Restaurants atmosphere is surrounded by the pond... Try get a seat next to the pond, Totally relaxing n cooling... Highly recommended...

Good ambient and service staffs. Ingredients used are fresh. Good choices in the menu. Am happy with the combination in each set menu. Like the taste and presentation. Portion served more than adequate. Repeat visit is a definite Yes. Thank you for serving me a complete meal.

Mutton briyani $10.50
Taste 2.5/10
I stay a block away and I will boycott this place.
Food is pretty good while service can improve
Prawns not clean properly before cooking. Disgusting. Will never come here again. Awful taste

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Visited on 25th June where dining is only allowed 2 per table. We are a family of 3 so we had to sit seperated. I giving 5 stars to their service! I wanted to ordered some food for sharing but we couldn't cross table for sure. And I definitely couldn't finished all the food on my own so the staff initiate to divide the food into 2 serving for us when overheard our conversation. Really appreciated their service especially during this period of time!
Always my biz lunch option. Wonderful service and great food.
Fast aervice, and friendly chef.
Wasn't as great as I've expected.. Still decent but not a refine dumpling restaurant. There are many better ones.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Lack of service with average good. Yet to improve.
Food is served quite quickly. Good service.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Love the food! Great staff as well. Usually crowded speacially weekends, but it's worth the wait!

Restaurant selling good selection of Malay cuisine. Quite popular with shoppers and those working in or around the mall. Hence, it can be difficult to get a seat/table during meal times. Best to come early/before or after the lunch and dinner crowd. Serving portion is alright.

Hearty main course. Sides are great too.
But one would need to endure 1 hour of waiting during the usual dinner hour.
See many customers ordering the fried rice combo. Will try on the next visit.
Food is good especially the tori teriyaki  bento set for $6.90. Only the aunty that prepare the food sound very rude. Well hope she Can be  more happy working and everyone happy eating!
Friendly staff and prata was good. I ordered egg and egg+onion prata. It was ready within 10 minutes. I have attached the latest menu for your reference. Last order 9.30pm.
Fun, interactive and yummy!

A hustling and bustling place with great prata (slightly crispy), drinks, curries. Staff is very welcoming. Plenty of seating. Parking is a bit of a challenge because the area has other restaurants and people come to hike the Peirce Reservoir. Highly recommended.

(Translated by Google) This restaurant serves mainly Sichuan Chinese cuisine. Individual restaurants are recommended for those who like Marvo tofu with Hanayama mushrooms. Also Sichuan-style tintin noodles in the photo? Has a high level of appearance and taste. I forgot the name of the dish in the photo, but you can see it on the menu table. I think whether you can enjoy a meal at a reasonable price regardless of day or night. There is also a private room for up to 10 people so you can enjoy it in groups.

Good food. Nice service. Poori was a little thick. Otherwise food was good. Service by the male staff was very good. The lady also was all smiles and good. They can make it better by simply cleaning tables and chairs well and sweeping the floor now and then. The washbasin can be kept cleaner too by running water now and then. Hope they don't loose their Indian cook and service staff. Both are awesome or have to get local Singaporean Indian shop soggy Thosai and bad service.

Malaysia Chiak! gives a very warmth environment to me with it's warm lightings and spacious seats.

The prawn mee I had is so tasty with very good soup base and fresh ingredients. The presentation is also attractive. The service is just nice for me. It also reminds me of the taste of prawn mee in Malaysia.

Their chendol ice is so so good! Red beans were big and juicy. The ice makes it chilled and crunchy. The chendol is also soft and smooth. The coconut milk also adds fragrance. Overall it's delicious!

I would highly recommend you to try their prawn mee if you are missing the taste of the prawn mee and chendol from Malaysia!

#ILoveMalaysiaChiak!
Love the food and service, recommend to friends
Not bad at all
We decided to try this restaurant and was overwhelmed by the wonderful Thai experience. It brings back wonderful memories of BKK. üòç I  will definitely recommend friends to drop by and try.

Yummy Chicken, Roasted Pork and Chashao pork. The options to have it with rice , noodle or koay teow is awesome! They have a few kind of steam soup such as watercress, lotus root and salted vegetable duck soap.
Reasonable prices for food taste. I love it.
What can I say? Food even better than shops in Golden Mile. That is the ultimate compliment! Great service too!
Srisun brand says it all..

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Queue: When I first reached at 10.30am, there was a queue. However, when I left there wasn't any queue.
Food: Good amount of varieties. The quality and taste of the food is average for me, not bad but not exceptionally nice.
Price: My family ordered 12 dim sum, 1 porridge, and 1 rice, for $53.00. Not too expensive but neither very cheap/affordable.

UPDATE: Went again this morning. Maybe because it was early in the morning and there was not a lot of customers, when my aunt went to order she was pressured by the staff into ordering additional items.
This is what I considered bad service. I never like the idea of being push into buying.
Affordable and nice. They fry your lok lok too!
3rd visit to Super Thai. Excellent dishes, at reasonable price. Servers are friendly too! Will try the oysters next time.
The service today is excellent! Has a team lunch here. From food recommendations and attentiveness of service.
Nice food everytime. Over the years their service improved, even though they are busy they still managed to serve us on time.

Got chased out of the place because we spent more than the 90 mins that was given to us.

I understand the logic when there's a long queue waiting for tables but what we are seeing is there's plenty of tables with no queue at all.

We were still taking our time to eat and intend to continue ordering more, but since their business is "so good" to the extent they need to chase customers out, i guess i have to find other options next time

excellent delicious indian food, also very value for money !
i LOVE their coin prata, and their veggie sides are a must try

Service on the slow side. Waited 20 minutes for a dosai when there were no customers at 5pm on a Saturday afternoon. Turned out they forgot the order.  Dosai was the "chewiest"  texture I have ever experienced for an egg dosai. Coconut chutney was tasty fresh and minty, dhal was thicker than most places (could actually see the dual!). Teh C kosong ice was disappointing though. Weak.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: The taste is so smooth and so rich. It is easy to prepare and I love to share this with my family and kids.
It have decent dishes for the rice but their meat dishes are over priced. The atmosphere is like a typical food court with old fashion decorations.

(Translated by Google) Rendang and Muar otah are very good. So is the rice egg flower.

(Original)
Rendang and Muar otah are very good. So is the bunga telam rice.

Waiting 45 min for our food, which then took less than 5 min to cook up after they realised we were forgotten. Tastes good, but fairly expensive for what it is, so probably consider if you have time to waste before coming here.

Splendid,the experience I had in this store is perfect.The service is commendable,the food was good,pricing was affordable,and the people there were very proactive,Everytime I finished my drink,they would immediately refill it regardless of iced or hot.In a nutshell,I am extremely satisfied with this store and will definitely come again.
Nice clean environment. Good variety of food at reasonable pricing.

Worst experience ever!!!!!!
We spend 7.4 for the laska burgers online
However, we waited for 40 mins!!!! Could you even believe it?? We were super disappointed in McDonalds in Singapore due o the awful service. We paid by Visa card and show the receipts, yet,  compensationMcDonald doesn‚Äôt believe it and insist that we are saying nonsense. They checked the records and say that there are no records!! We almost couldn‚Äôt receive our burgers because of their lack of understanding and bad service!!!!! They even looks like that they don‚Äôt believe in us at the end even if we show them the receipt of visa card(also the message) Surely, we deserves a compensation! How could Mc Donald‚Äôs waste our time and being so demanding and mean to us! Please apologize to us. We feel awful. This McDonald doesn‚Äôt even deserves a visit guys

Taste is just ok. $14 for a bowl of lomi is overpriced for me, must be because of the generous portion of meat. Think more chicharon and fishballls could be better. But all in all, I still love La Cafe!

Expect half the menu to be out of stock.
