The waitress claimed it is because today ‚Äúbusiness was too good‚Äù. Excuse me, we have been sitting here since 7pm and your restaurant has not been full at any point of time.

At 8.30pm, they are left with 3 dessert options out of a list of more than 12. That‚Äôs 25%
Chicken cutlet is the best value for money. It is super crunchy and the portion is so big I could never finish in one sitting. The rest like chicken chop and fish and chips are ok only.

Good food. I think it's better than Nakhon Thai.

$26.50 for Cashew chicken + Mixed Vege + Tom Yum Soup + Tomyum Fried Rice.

My weekly fix of fishball noodle. My go to place with my wife. Fishball and fishcake are all handmade. It's totally different from other stalls which use factory made fishball and fish cake. Quantity of noodles at $4 is generous.

Had the platter with 3 meats (lamb, beef & pork) and they were all delicious but i must say the lamb pale to comparison with the other 2 (and it‚Äôs more expensive). The pasta was cooked to al dente although I feel the flavour can be stronger abit (it‚Äôs only $5.50 by the way). This meal costed us about $37.50 but the portion was quite generous (definitely enough for 2) and there are 2 side dishes that came with the platter (we had mash potato and sweet Potato). Overall quite worth the price and the food are good.
Decor was interesting so gave it a try but food was average. Tom yum soup, Kang Kong n pork basil rice were passable. Can skip the vermicelli salad n oyster omelette.

Nice cozy restaurant that served very good Shanghainese food. The soup dumpling, pan fried bun, braised pork bun and spring roll are must try snacks at this restaurant. The chicken mushroom noodle is very also a must try spicy dish. Do take note that it is better to make reservations if you want to eat at this restaurant.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content:
(Translated by Google) Sambal Sotong and Red Meat was nice.

(Original)
Sambal Sotong and Daging Merah was nice.

Queued 45mins to get in during lunch hours on frid. Lack of staff. Food came quite fast after ordering so ok. Missed out the water i ordered... But Bolognase Cheese Fries quite nice. Fish is very plain but crispy. Have to eat w the sauce. Soup of the day was cauliflower soup which comes w the garlic bread. My friend like the chicken alfredo. Not so much the chicken but the pasta was nice. (forgot to take photo). Wont be back again sorry.

Taste good, price good.
Thai green chilly source excellent

2nd visit. The pork Cutlet is very nice, thick cut and the meat still quite juicy. Change the rating to 4 star instead.

Average tasting Western food stall. Less crowded compare to the other western food stall in the same market, so it an alternate if you prefer shorter waiting time.
Recent visited.. was disappointed with the lamb shank, it was not even warn..like a cold dish..Taste also very blend... disappointed and so expensive... However egg prata was still good...
Food is okay. The service staff blocked out the entire row of seats near the window citing that is reserved for their staff only to open it up after 5 min when more customers came in.
The Best Mee Goreng I have ever tasted. You gotta try it you won't regret it üëçüëçüëçüå∂üå∂üå∂üòä
Delicious Chinese food! The fried dumpling and xiao long bao are a MUST TRY!
V good!

Ordered the set for 4 which is about $40+
The meats are well marinated but I find the greens are lacking but add a veg set ard $4+.
The condiments are standard.
The setup is in coffeeshop in the light industrial area vicinity. There are many stalls to add on to mookata. I liked the vibes due to the music and the young crowd.
However not all the fans are working so try to find near it or else you find yourself perspiring while eating mookata

Sushi wasn‚Äôt special or exceptionally good but it‚Äôs a nice place for ‚Äòtrain served‚Äô sushi. Price was reasonable but not as economic as other express sushi place. Would recommend to try if you want to have sushi while you‚Äôre in the area but definitely won‚Äôt travel to eat there deliberately.

i stay few blocks away and i eat quite often. recently, the standard has dropped a lot. dont deserve to be top zi char list. maybe they have changed the chef, but the taste is not up to standard. sweet and sour pork may not be their signature but is a common dish, i was disappointed that the meat is terribly small, meaning you eat more flour. the sauce for black pepper pork chop is diluted as well.
Pretty gd prata, curry watery but OK. First time coming here, a little ex.

Had dinner here today. Ordered a teriyaki don. The rice is terrible. Japanese rice cook until texture like porridge. They replaced but rice still the same. Not recommended. How can the chef serve this kind of food to its customer.

Always loved springleaf! Patronised the ones in the West. And first time trying this. The food quality is bad. The mee goreng didn‚Äôt taste a tiny bit like how it should be. And the egg Prata was mehhh. This was totally not the standard it should be. The noodle was so bad that we poured fish curry over it to give it some flavour as it was very bland. Would not recommend this outlet.

the location here is very convenient.
Great food and service. Has a very reasonably priced set meal of all their specialties. Assam fish is a must have!
Dine with Family. Nice ambience

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Great place to bring parents & families who love good quality chinese food. The place is known for their "orh lua" and cold crab üëç If you're into desserts, try out the bird nest served in almond & coconut (pretty interesting and palatable!). Overall great service, highly recommended ‚ò∫Ô∏è

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content:
The steam fish was perfectly cooked, highly recommend. Crawfish was pretty good. Eggplant also solid.

The cauliflower was bland.

Ordered rib eye steak medium rare from this restaurant today. Got a seared steak with completely raw meat!!!! Could not eat the rest of the meal as I am not sure how fresh is the meat. Everything was horrible.

Had a quick lunch at Putien and looks like they had revamped the menu. I‚Äôve asked to veganized these dishes and was pleased to find the dishes were still very flavorful and delicious.
Staff are well informed of the term vegetarian and vegan making the order taking such a breeze.

Very nice service took the menu to come serve us to speed up the process! Thai milk tea a must to order!
Love the service and the food!

Food is salty without flavour.

Salt and soy sauce should not be used as substitutes for dashi stock.

We walked in without reservation at 2pm on a Sunday afternoon in Dec 2021 and there were many available tables.  Service was pleasant and prompt.

We ordered several dishes including the Chicken Hotpot, Griddle Cabbage with Pork, Spicy Fried Chicken, Tomato Eggs, and some assorted skewers.  Out of all the food, only the skewers were good.

The Chicken Hotpot was very disappointing, it was oily and the chicken were mostly chicken bones with little meat.  We ordered the Large portion but it was very little.  We had to add a plate of spicy fried chicken as there was very little meat.

The Griddle Cabbage was very oily, serving was small, and there were only 3 small slices of pork in it.

Tomato Egg was too salty and we needed rice to go with it.  We probably wont visit again in the near future, but if we do, we will probably only go for the skewers.

Total pax: 4
Total cost: $130 (food, with 2 botts of beer and 1 llum juice)

My first visit here. Seems like all the staff at this stall were family members or close relatives... and they were friendly and courteous. This makes for a pleasant experience. +1 for this stall... I will certainly come again. Mi rebus, mi siam & lontong were a little "sweetish" for me... prolly meant for those who couldn't take spicy stuff. The $1 nasi lemak ($1.50 if you want both fish + ikan bilis) was good enough; what do you expect for this price at this day & age..? Well done to the stall owner & staff! üëç
Came for weekend buffet lunch. Food was good, especially the chili crab. Good varity and fresh. Recommend the seabass.

Had the 7.9 butter byrani special. Four plus pieces of chicken in huge rice portion, salty crisp, pickles, and chutney. Tables a bit dirty but big crowd during early dinnner hour. Tasted pretty good but it is mall prices so a bit higher than in Indian town in the city.

Do reserve before going especially on a weekend as it can get packed.

First visit - Order didn't go through the online ordering system and we ended up waiting for awhile to realise it didn't go through. But technical fault, can't be helped. Anyway, reordered and our food came in adequate time. The spinach cream pasta was quite nice.

Second visit - Decided to try the otah, and sakura pasta. Interesting menu, both were alright.

In both visits, the drinks were slightly underwhelming. Nice atmosphere and staff though!

Am a regular client of this stall. Even that I am not spared but to suffer very bad service and rude attitude from the lady taking orders today. We ordered our simple dine in meal together with take away. It was about 6pm. Not busy hour yet. The dine in food came really fast. After we finished, the take away was not ready. I was surprised. No choice but wait. End up, I was made to wait another 15 to 20 minutes for the take away. Not only that, one of the orders was wrong. Êñ∞Ê¥≤Á±≥Á≤â became Êñ∞Ê¥≤Ê≤≥Á≤â. May be I mountain tortoise, never know Êñ∞Ê¥≤Ê≤≥Á≤â ever existed. In a not so polite manner, she said she will change for me. But I am not prepared to wait another 15 mintues to change the order. And she argued and lied with a straight face saying my wife told her to start preparing the take away only after we finished our meals. Wonder who in the right mind would do that in a coffee shop Zichar stall with smoking corner just a few steps away. Without my wife to verify on the spot as she already left to run some errands, I had to take the lady's word, and left, not so happy of course. Obviously my wife did not tell her that.
Everyone makes mistakes. Just admit with the correct attitude. No big deal. Why tell lies to cover a mistake? Moreover, to a regular client.

The food tastes good, but there wasn't the wow factor i was hoping for.  Service is attentive but standard. Place very cold, just feel like quickly leave the place after the meal. Prawns for peng cai do not taste well, manager said it could be overcooked n apologise for it.
Food not really nice and environment is not cosy!
Reasonably priced. Ordered a beef ribeye don. The beef cubes grilled OK. Overall, it was kind of dry.
One of the best Mee Rebus in town! Generous portion and value for money! They add Satay Sauce on top which really complements the Mee Rebus very well!
good ambience and fast serving . The menu is wide spread , love the yam and bee Hoon ,lor men.

Ordered a Tom yam noodle soup, non spicy clear pork (ball) soup, mango salad, cold Thai milk tea and fresh coconut, between the two of us and the bill only came up to $27.80. The salad was crunchy, and had the right bland of spiciness and soreness. The Tom yang noodle soup was lovely as well. The clear pork soup. . I like my soup spicy so between two soup I much prefer the tom. Yang, however th epotk balls were very moist and tasty and I'm sure kids would that. I'm going back again for  sure.
Not so great even merged with boon lay nasi lemak ..food not cooked fully .

Been eons since I've stepped into this pre-loaded eatery and now rekindled (I've joined their memebership), not because of vouchers but the meals are value for money, and if like me, you like a little nostalgia from time to time, this is one the places. Try their lunch sets, fast serving and decent portions with no overkill. I had mine in AMK. Upgrade to bisque soup for a change. Come here for a quiet anniversary or dates.  As their slogan says, it's steak and more...
Awesome food
Great tasting food!.

Definitely consistent of deep fried crispy chicken cutlet.
Indeed a good idea to order with pasta.

I‚Äôm a huge Thai cuisine lover and usually as long as the taste meets the minimal bench mark I‚Äôm pretty much satisfied. This one is horrible! Pls don‚Äôt waste your money and time to try this place out. Will definitely not be back again
Authentic Hakka food that is delicious and affordable as well! Very homely environment and portions are generous even for the small orders. Love the complimentary dessert as well.

Good attention, variety of dishes. Amazing curly fries. Big menu.
A lot of sugar in the cold tea, like a heavy syrup, not recommended.

Everything here, from simple pineapple fried rice, fried kang Kong with sambal, basil pork, fish cake, to iced Thai milk tea and dessert red ruby, everything is authentic Thai food and very delicious. I wish I had a bottomless stomach to try all the dishes here! Will definitely come back again for Tomyam Soup, Pad Thai and other stuff!

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Would have given 0 star I could even do that. Horrible experience and service at the restaurant. Twice they messed my reservations and were not apologetic about it. Even though they might have seats, they would rather entertain walk in from Koreans, than offer the seats to us. We had a heavily pregnant diner in our group and all they can tell us is go stand elsewhere and not block them while they check what went wrong (which obviously was not solved). So if you are local, don‚Äôt bother to reserve because they won‚Äôt honor the reservation anyway, and will put the blame on you. Twice it was messed up by their Filipino staff Aida (sorry not sure how to spell her name so got to say her nationality but they only have 1 Filipino staff) so just be careful even if you still want to proceed to reserve. Make sure you check if it‚Äôs her, if yes, please ask for another staff to prevent yourself the agony of standing in the restaurant and getting maligned and blamed for their own staff mistake. Go at your own risk (of spoiling your plan and mood). Honestly, there are other better options just around with much friendlier staff and better service like Itaewon Jjajang, or even obba jjajang!
Food was nice. Service is good. But quite pricey for a private dining restaurant which have kopitiam chairs as seats.

Had the CNY set meal for 2 pax, must say that we were pretty disappointed with the food quality. Fish was not fresh, other dishes were mediocre or too salty. Dessert supposed to be birds nest but didn‚Äôt see any birds nest and it‚Äôs overly sweet.

Tanoke is located on the second floor on a shophouse.  We decided to drop by as the other popular restaurants were full but we are happy with what life brought us.

First the service, Mr Rao was there to follow up on the food and ensuring our water glass is never half filled.  In fact, for one of the dishes, he noticed that something was amiss and brought it back to the kitchen.  So this is someone who takes pride in his work.

We opted for the Happy hour sake which comes with a mini wagyu burger and burdock chips.  A good start.  We went for the set and it is extremely well priced as it comes with 2 appetizers(one of which is a hamachi carpaccio), 2 gigantic desserts, a substantial portion of 3 types of wagyu and a few other items.  Hubby and I both enjoyed the Kagoshima ribeye the most.

All in all, a great find and I hope more people will appreciate them to keep them in business.  Not every restaurant has earned this but I feel they have.
Value for money. Previously at S11 amk Central. This hainanese western stall is a classic example of simple Western  food goodness. Uncle and Aunty still same same.
Good food, clean place. Table service available
Cai poh tofu so good. Salted fish fried rice was yummy too. They are generous with the salted fish. So flavourful

$24 bucks for chicken rice for 2.  Chicken is stone cold and still bloody.  Rice is dry and hard. Cashless now so inconvenient have to pay thru the app where they capture your info and then annoy you with marketing.  What a disaster RWS has become.

Personally this is the worse nasi lemak I've ever eaten in my life

1. The pandan green colour rice looks good but didn't even have a hint of pandan fragrance in the rice. I wonder if they're using pandan colouring instead of natural pandan leaves?

2. The rice they used seems like low quality as it is firm and dry.

3. Chilli is too watery and doesn't blend well with the rice.

4. Chicken wing is too tiny like a quail

5. Tempe and fish is so-so

First time trying the fish steamboat and it was delicious. Had the whole grouper where the meat is fillet to cook separately. The head and bones were deep fried and cooked in the broth with lots of vegetables, tofu and yam. Pair with the sambal belacan adds flavour to the veg and tofu.
Reasonably priced western food.
Rmb to call and pre order. Else there will be chicken wing eet
Nice place to chill but snacks is expensive and average tasting.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Average chinese cuisine in TPY. XLB's skin is a tad too thick but the meat filling is decent while the different flavours (normal, black truffle, chili crab and salted egg) are interesting. Generally fine though the dessert (red bean pastry) is a nice end to the meal with the crust light and crispy.
Standard still maintained since the last time i came here 10 years ago. Best mee rebus.
Good Excellent fanatastic what else to describe their food.
Delicious bowl of chicken leg ramen ($6.50)! Meat falls right off the bone. Broth was tasty. Ramen‚Äôs taste reminded me of yellow noodle. Will go back again if I‚Äôm in the area!
Fried rice was decent compare to other hawer centre shops ..

Quick and decent meal.
Rice: not fragrant enough
Rendang: average, wished it was more tender.

It seems like there are different sambal to choose from. I had the sambal xo and felt it was awesome.
Having great time with my friend here, the foods are not bad.

It is too crowded during weekend lunch and long queue. Food is just average. Only nasi lemak and chicken wing/cutlet is recommended. The rest are really average i.e. curry noodles, rojak.  Not really worth the queue. The Anson Chu Chang Fen is disappointing... the heung piah and daosa piah worth try as it is fresh.
Authentic homecooked food. Had their vegetarian set and it was great! Vadais were nice and crispy and the chutney was delicious. Will def go back again
Food here are really yummy, I recommend the herbal soup, vegetarian creamy soup, and snack sugary yam ÔºàÁ≥ñÈúúËäãÂ§¥Ôºâ.

Cashier staff today (9th Aug) had a subpar attitude. I paid using paywave and it did not go through the first time (machine fault or sth) bc the second time I used the same card for the transaction it went through. Cashier felt the need to announce loudly that my card was not working after the first failed transaction, whatever. During the second time I paid using the same card and the transaction went through (machine showed approved but cashier wasn‚Äôt looking) but right as the transaction went through, there was a power outage throughout the restaurant (second time within 20 mins btw). After the power came back on, cashier told me to tap my card again and I informed her the transaction already went through. I showed her that I already have a payment made to the restaurant (via my GRAB app), she kept saying it didn‚Äôt show up on her machine so I need to pay again. The fact that there was no transaction shown on the machine wasn‚Äôt her fault but her attitude was really terrible to be in customer service, she didn‚Äôt bother explaining or try to be empathetic. As a customer I already paid so obviously I wasn‚Äôt keen to pay twice and have to wait for one of the payments to be refunded to me. She took down my name and number and said she will contact her bank to refund the payment to me so I‚Äôll need to keep an eye out for that. Could train your staff to be better at having some empathy or just have better customer service :)

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Taste quite authentic Malaysian style dim sum.
Particularly like the yong tou foo which reminds me of old days üòã though a bit pricy ($1/piece in average)
Char Siew bun and Egg Tarts are nice too.

Fantastic Tex-Mex Sandwiches at AFFORDABLE prices!!!
Signature Pulled Pork Sandwich at just S$4.00!!! Expensive? Think again, where can you find pulled pork of this quality at this price?
O.O

Try it to believe it!

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content:
Went for lunch around 12:45pm on a Sunday and it was fairly empty.

Upon ordering was shared that a number of items were only available in the evening and quite a number not available from the lunch menu (odd for a newly opened restaurant).

Waited close to an hour for our food to come, a family that arrived after us had ordered, ate and paid the bill to leave.

After a good long wait one staff told us that the rice we ordered can't be fulfilled as they have multiple orders in the kitchen (not sure why this was told to us after waiting so long and why it our order that was depriortized when we were the first few to come).

Food finally came, it was subpar some parts seasoned with too much salt and drinks too sweet.

Towards the end we checked on our takeaway item as well and noticed some back and forth- am assuming that order wasn't put in and that the chef just threw the ingredients together to make it then and there.

Shared our disappointment with the counter staff when paying and he told us the long wait was due to the soup my mum had ordered which doesn't make any sense because that was the first item to arrive.

First and last time here.

Might be my personal bad experience as it's a newly opened store.
Nice place for roast duck and char siew(recommendation is to order the streaky version aka ÂçäËÇ•ÂèâÁÉß). Comes with a side bowl of thick & flavourful umami gravy to drizzle on white rice.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
Coffee stall lasts forever, nearly 30 years Qing Qing.
Pretty plenty of choices for youngsters in bean curb, jelly, Teck Hwa. Market and hawker are modernised with bright lit stall.
Found little old style fried prawn here, ËÆ∞ÂæóÊù•ÂêÉ„ÄÇ
Food center is well lit and ventilated.
Delicious Ramen on hawker with good price
Best authentic Thai food you can get in Singapore which is cheap. Not service and gst charge. If you love cockles, this is the place to go.
Quick no frills lunch spot.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Wanted to order from a new place to try out. This was recommended from one of my friends and turned out to be a great choice. The food is authentic Indian and rightly priced. Can wait for Dine-in to start to go over to the place with family and friends. The butter Chicken and Chicken Lollipop are must try.
Love the authentic chinese food! Price is very reasonable. Must try the dumplings!

Athantic malayale style cusine...good taste.. restaurant flavours with moderate price. Taste was super ..will visit again with friends..as the quantity they serve is good enough to share . We have pick with limited items but it will tempt to chose all ...so may not be one visit enough..

Delicious chilli ban mian. Initially I thought there's not enough chilli and sauce. But after stirring, each and every strand of the noodles was coated immensely with the sauce. There was pork lard to go with it too. It was marvellous. At $4.50 in this setting, it's very worth the price.
Apparently they have quite a spread of mains and sides. Lookout for their promotion.
Food is Good. Volcano Chicken is a must. Seafood is very fresh. Service is excellence.
Superb food quality and customer service as always. Food is served on time and hot. Never fail to impress me @ NPC.

Sometimes eat.
Taste is same like nasi padang
super nice lamb chops
Today is my first time trying out the yakitori..chicken ball n ckicken tori...not too bad...üôÇ

OMG!! Went at 6pm, the first batch of food served at around 1.5-2hrs later. After we went off around 9pm, 3 of us were not even 3 quarter full. Reached home & ate tibits some more. This is really too much!! Being a restaurant at hotel, the quantity & quality of food should not be like this. I thought that the chefs are really very busy cooking so by right, the food should be very hot when served, right? but surprisingly the food are cold??!! What happened? Some more the taste is not flavourful. In my perspective, I have got feeling that the restaurant direction is‚Ä¶ you, customers come in, welcome you, being seated, my premise is big enough, you wait for your food to be served, I have plenty of time, but I‚Äôm not sure if you have the time, I will serve the food very slowly, if you cannot wait, please settle the payment & proceed to the door. As for the food, for instance, crispy fish skin, obviously it is purchased from outside & not prepared by the restaurant. When asked for another plates, they told you‚Ä¶ no more Liao. To be frank lah, anyone wants to treat ne to the restaurant again, thank you and I will say NO! Can you imagine, went for buffet & yet, eat until no full. Si buay ke lian

A nice restaurant with great food. Love the cockles here and their fried garlic pork. Best of all, it is a good place to chill at the famous Hangout with these food to enjoy the sunset after a long day at work. Will be back again.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: A long standing Chicken Rice establishment in the Novena area. Rice is quite good and chicken is decent taking into account the current supply constraints. Above average overall and one of the better ones around.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: A perfect restaurant for Indian vegetarian cuisine. Homemade taste.

The sliced pork porridge is thick and flavourful. We ordered a set hence there were you tiao and soya bean milk. The fried fritters and soya bean milk were average. The claypot liver had a few thick slices of liver but they were bland, only the sauce was nice. If you like porridge, then this is the place for you as there are many different choices of porridge (seafood, chicken, scallops, pork etc.)to select from and the dishes came quickly. Service was good.

I doubt the authenticity of this Japanese place but this have not stopped me from coming here over the past 10 years. I like the simplicity of their food and warm vibe of the place itself. My absolute favourite is their Zaru soba which is seemingly simple but deceivingly delicious. Go for their kani mayo sushi too with 2 big generous servings of crabmeat mayo at just a few dollars.
I never leave this place feeling dissatisfied.
The prices are not stable here. Indian food is expensive here if compared to other Indian food outlets. Try Chicken Tikka Murtabak here.
Food is nice. But lack customer service. Service is slow and there is no attention to customer needs. Had to wait for a long time to be served. Asked to eat in and they packed.

I had the Wanton Mee and Chendol, the chendol was acceptable, don't think they used gula melaka. The wanton mee was bad, mainly due to the soup, like they kept around for too many days. The pork looked beautiful, but tasted bad also. Don't order the wanton mee. The staff was also rude, but that seemed to be keeping with the quality of the place.
The flavours were ok but the quality and freshness not really there. The best dishes were the beef Thai green curry and the fish cake.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: I used to visit this place but haven‚Äôt been back in a while. Decided to have lunch here. The soup for Dan Dan mian was way too thick, and spicy too. Don‚Äôt mind the spiciness, but the soup was a too ‚Äújelak‚Äù. Order the fried duck, it was good. But portion is too small for the price I feel. The salted egg custard bao was the best dish we had. Hence the 3 stars.

Super slow yet food nothing special. Cook was packing precooked spaghetti (horrible, they should be cooked fresh) into about 50 small bags for later use instead of spending time to preparing my order.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: ordered this for $8.50? 11 SMALL chicken? you feeding who? ur mother ah? rude staffs. claims 24hours but everything dont have. dont know if they‚Äôre purely lazy or what. first time coming here and i am regretting it he moment i see the people. took forever for food to come. waited 30mins for 2 naan. ridiculous.

This place serves the most yummy & reasonable BBQ meat, and especially my favourite beef cuts. The staff service was also very courteous & meticulous during my visit.

As it‚Äôs a fairly new concept of a self-service outlet from their other outlets, there‚Äôs always areas of improvement. I just hope people are not so quick to criticise the staff & or systems, but rather to provide more positive & encouraging words for their growth. Everyone needs a ‚Äúbooster‚Äù now & then for continuous development.

Personally, it‚Äôs an awesome place to have BBQ meals with loved ones & worth the wait. Keep up the good work, peeps of Yakiniku Like @ AMK Hub!!! Don‚Äôt let negativity get to you but show them otherwise! Gambat√©!!! üí™üèºüëåüèº‚ò∫Ô∏è

Love this place! The noodles taste like Yong Peng noodles. The pork lard goes very well with he noodles! Noodles don't have alkaline taste. Belachan is on the sour side. Their fishballs has a fishy taste. Not my type. Fishcake is not bad. All are handmade. Came at early 8 plus on sat morn but still need to queue for about 25 mins. Noodle portion quite big! Saw the uncle doing ice bath for the noodles too
I order pick up from food panda, and the item late for 35-40 mins from the agreed time. Poor management!

This restaurant is famously known for their claypot rice, but imo, the beehoon taste better.

Thai style yong tou foo is overly oily due to their ingredients are deepfried. Salted egg bitterground is very tasty and doesnt taste like bitterground at all.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Food is expensive and not nice at all. Ordered their Prawn Paste Chicken Wing, and Fried Pork Belly, both were subpar and has a bad oil smell/taste to them. But however staffs were attentive and friendly :)

Situated at level 3 of Safra Toa Payoh, this place consists of at least 3 ballrooms which are customized for different events as listed on their website. I was there for a wedding, and there was also a D&D happening. Food was mostly good while service can be improved. Note that my experience is that of during a wedding.
Special ice cream couldn't find such unique ice cream in sg! Only at MBK Thai. Ice cream better than shops at upper Thomson

The Yakitori is a must try. Chef did the chicken just done. Cooked and Juicy. A true Gem in the west.
Extensive Sake and Shochu menu.

I hate myself for finding this place this late. Please don‚Äôt come here so I will always find a seat whenever I am here. True Gem.
Very satisfied!!!Highly recommend ‚ò∫Ô∏è

Dim Sum is affordable and tasty too! Worth it!. Their Chai Por Hor Fun (dried radish hor fun) has much wok hei and flavour.

The fish soup been hoon is done with long hours of brewing fish bones. They don't skimp on raw ingredients.

First of all, amazing alfresco setting. My partner and I went during weekend lunch and fortunately it wasn‚Äôt that crowded. Able to enjoy the peace and nature in a well-ventilated place. I like how the restaurant is well maintain and there‚Äôs a small washing area with soap and sanitizer for those who were in the outdoor seats area.

I only see 2 service staff during our visit. Not sure if the restaurant is understaffed because you need some patience to get their attention at times. Otherwise no complain about the service.

Food wise, the price is definitely on the much higher side and we were glad that the food quality and taste justify the price paid - except the dessert. Simple cake, ice cream and sweet red bean cost $15++ which I thought it‚Äôs way too overpriced. 2 simple appetizers, 2 assorted plates and a dessert set us off slightly above $100.

Overall it was a satisfying meal. Maybe will come back again for the ambience and to try the sake and beer.
Good atmosphere. Great service. Friendly staff. Good food.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Bought nasi goreng Pattaya for $7 only get 1/3 of riceüòë

This is a halal cafe which serves western food. The set up is simple and prices are reasonable for the portions. I had the chicken cutlet with pepper sauce on a hot plate. It was served with a good portion of mashed potato which had the sauce in an indentation in the middle. Nice presentation.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Reasonably priced and tasted good in general.  There are many choice for dishes of fish, chicken, squid, beef and et.  Like many said, avoid lunch hours, the Q can be very long, and you will likely have negative impression on the hospitality.  The sambal offered wasn't spicy to me, but you might think otherwise.

Lastly, will I visit the shop again? if I am visiting the area, probably yes, otherwise don't think I will travel far just to eat here.  :D
Nice outdoor chill out area. Food was reasonably priced (especially with SAFRA discount), albeit rather salty.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: V teochew clan establishment with many familiar dishes

Went on a Thursday evening and the space was quiet and serene! A lot of space between tables which made it a plus for an already dog friendly establishment. Service staff were attentive and responsive. Ordered three mains: Sakura ebi tagliatelle, seafood aglio olio and a small breakfast plate, found them all to be nice! Hot latte was also good! But apple crumble was very disappointing cos it was soft and mushy, hence minus one star!

Ordered Rib Eyes steak - texture is very good. Chicken chop fried rice was different from Pic and rice has very good aroma.

Value for money
Average food...low grade outlet

Head over just for the chilli ban mian! One of my favourite dishes at Malaysia Chiak! Stores are awkwardly placed cause of the limited space but they have all the dishes that the rest of the outlets have! Same old taste:) The picture is a bit misleading cause of the egg, its hard boiled instead of soft boil! I prefer the soft boil egg üëç Vegetable is also raw in the picture (not as per illustrated) but the dish taste never fails! A must try if you head over to Malaysia Chiak!
Quiet place so can avoid crowds and yet have Chinese food. Came on public holiday during lunch. There are promotion & unique dishes too.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
So so, nothing special.

Average per pax $15, acceptable range however quality dropped significantly especially the chicken itself.

Salted egg pork ribs and Sambal Sotong doesn't impress us as well, especially salted egg pork ribs a bit disappointed as other outlet at Yishun much much better taste compare with this outlet.

In overall, 3 Star for the food quality, 4 Star for the warm services and spacious environment.

Sadly to say, I won't recommend this place to others. In fact, we grave for their signature chicken but maybe, we just shouldn't pay too high expectations.
Nice local western food place. Had the burger. Not bad.
Please make it 24 hours like the branch at NeWest!!!

4.5 stars. Been wanting to eat here and we regretted not coming here earlier. Came at 5 plus in the evening on a weekday and there was no crowd. Ordered sweet and sour pork, hokkien noodles and kai lan with salted fish. The dishes arrived quickly. The sweet and sour pork wowed us, succulent, crispy and juicy, with pieces of pineapples and tomatoes. The other dishes were delicious too and the portions were huge. Love the vegetables, very fresh and crunchy, with fragrant pieces of salted fish. The noodles were nicely done with wok-hei. Belacan chilli was good and spicy. Would definitely return to try the other dishes!

This is an institution! It's got that precious old school charm/ vibe, and the food doesn't disappoint, nor the warm/ friendly service from the stately hosts. Ê≤πÈ∫¶ËèúÔºåÊ¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâÔºåÂÆ¢ÂÆ∂ÁÇíÈù¢ were all very good, and still a handful of menu items we've not been able to order/ try. The patronage on a Friday evening seemed good and I hope the good business continues, so our local culinary scene could stay vibrant - especially with restaurants like this.

Been here a few times. Go for their curry chicken (enough to share for 2 small eater), salad (well balanced texture and taste; good for sharing between 2 to 4) and their fried rice and spaghetti / noodles dishes. Give their burger a miss (chicken one was made of minced meat patty that is mushy and taste bad; It would be better if the meat is the chicken chop or cutlet type).

Chanced upon this thai food restaurant and decided to give it a try, the food tastes so authentic and the time that took the food to be served is almost immediate! The staffs there were super nice and pay great attention to our needs! I will come back to try more food on the menu! üëçüèª

First time dining there last Thursday and it was a wonderful experience because all the (aunties and uncle) staff were polite and I felt that they provided a better service than many waiters and waitresses at a lot of the restaurants my family and I had been to in Singapore. We had a toddler with us and the staff were patient despite him dropping some things on the floor a few times. They also came over a few times to check on our toddler and to play with him. The food was delicious and portion size was fine except for the Bian Rou dumpling soup as it the dumplings were pretty small and there was very little vegetables in it.

Cold plate was very generous in portion . ‰∏úÂù°ËÇâ was ok flavour is there tender and nice. The È∫¶Áâá‰∏ã was dry and blend shouldn‚Äôt order the one without shell. ËèúÂåÖÈ∏° was acceptable but I feel the chicken inside was lack of flavour and abit bland have to go with the sauce to taste . I love the 2 wok fried vegetable .

awesome place for ‰∏≤‰∏≤ and hot pot stuff !

nice food , reasonable prices for food abd beer!

recommended!

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Delicious food. Asparagus is a must order. Fried meesuah is superb! Braised duck, especially the sauce, was yummy with rice. Braised tofu was fresh and tasty. Abalone recommended. Ngoh hiang the five spice taste is too strong, so only order if you like it strong. Pomfret fish is very fresh but tastes bland. Cai po fried kway teow was overcooked, too bitter as it was cooked beyond the wok hey stage. Oyster omelette was good. Appetiser tea was great. Salted egg prawns were brilliant and a must order too. Would come back again to try other dishes.

Good authentic Chinese food, friendly staffs too.
Mapo doufu and Dry-Fried Long Beans are some of my personal favorites, they do takeaway delivery too with Grabfood/Foodpanda

Great ambience and cosy. The restaurant wasn‚Äôt too noisy and ideal for family and couple. Food was alright and a bit pricey. No drinks was served and we have to pay for chilliü§™. Service staffs are friendly esp the guy in white and the humorous lady with black rim specs. Overall my family enjoyed ourselves and the beautiful surrounding.

Very rude service staff,  shouted at me many times. First time shouted at me telling me that my food is ready when I haven't even ordered. Second asking what I wanted to ordered. And lastly he kept shouting a number and while I was checking my receipt number explained very rudely that the number is the food I ordered. Food is decent pepper lunch standard but service is really bad.

Plain and egg pratas are usually pre-made and not upon order hence cold and soggy.  New order made was not fulfilled and staff is on mobile phone and rest try to look busy.  Overall experience is bad and left with an empty stomach.

Amazing food!!!

Had the Konoha sannin set:
1) A5 miyazaki wagyu ribcap 120g - the beef was really soft & tender! Also quite fun how we can torch our own meat and add the toppings up our preference!
2) Crispy pork tonkatsu - Super good?! It‚Äôs crispy yet not oily and so flavorful! Better than tonkatsu specialty places actually...
3) Torched shime saba - super good too and flavorful! I also like how it‚Äôs fillet so it doesn‚Äôt have a ton of bones!!
4) Side dishes - the chuka kurage (jellyfish) was fragrant with the sesame oil, and potato salad is always a favourite!
5) Onsen egg rice (add on) & miso soup - I like how the rice has onsen egg and furikake on it

Overall, each dish was great on its own. Really loved the food and will give 5/5!! Also interesting with all the Naruto deco! Recommend!!

Delicious food! Amazing service!! Very satisfied with the meal and kindness shown. Highly recommend if you‚Äôre looking for authentic Indian food in Singapore! You won‚Äôt be able to find this kind of authenticity anywhere else! 10/10 recommend!

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Nice n adorable madeleines and big crossiants at this stall. Madeleines were fresh out of oven when I visited at 9 plus in e morning. Run by a young hawker and they sell waffles, ice cream n pasta too.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Like the coffee.
A mixture of Chinese n Malay food available
It's ok
Good food for the price range. Free set meal upgrade for lunch time.
Amazing food selection with the upgraded choice of japanese canned drinks
Attentive staff and quite decent food
Their prawn mee and Asam Laksa are the closest flavor to eating in Malaysia! So good and authentic taste.  I always come here if I want to eat those flavors!
Seats are very limited though food is not bad, their tea & coffee are good

Very comfortable environment.  unique and special.  Like a garden different with other Chinese restaurant.
Food are authentic.  Tasty. Potion enough for us.  Worth to try
Great hokkien/ Cantonese dishes for family gathering. Good service. Outdoor tables available with wheelchairs access

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: Nice and budget friendly Sushi

Casual Chinese restaurant with indoor and outdoor seating. Serves all the classic dishes like fried noodles /rice, stir fries, braised dishes, seafood, etc. Their house made tofu, whole roast chicken, yam basket, and braised pork buns are worth trying. There is a clean toilet for customers as well. Can be crowded on weekends (pre-covid), so work booking a table ahead.
Nice south indian food and cosy dine in....

Just had dinner here . Nothing special about this restaurant. Food is normal
There are ala carte and set for you to choose with other side dishes. Plenty to choose
Prices depend on what type of food you choose.
Happy eating happy life !!!

0 would be my rating for their staff impolite and impatient attitude especially two of the short hair ladies (one is the cashier and another is the waitress). I went here twice and each time an incident will happen. They are rude, have no manners, and poor services. I will never come to this restaurant again! Good luck to their business!

So good!! The pork was super tender and soft and not overly sweet, while the sashimi was super fresh and sliced thick enough too! Visited on a sat lunch, was crowded but didnt have to wait long for the food to be served. Will definitely be back to try the other dons.

Edit: 2nd visit and dropped to 4 stars. I'm not too sure why it didnt come with miso soup and sides this time round. Wondering if it was missed out or it is only for lunch. Was very satisfied with the sashimi as it was thick cut and very fresh, but sadly disappointed with the squid as the sauce was way too much and making it overly sweet. The squid was actually cooked to perfection though.. not too chewy. I will still go back again to try more mains and hopefully give back the 1 star again.
One of the worst beef donburi I had. The sauce was bad, beef was bland. Will not be back.

Reached the store at 9.30am and it was already crowded, about 60% of the seats were taken up. I ordered one egg and one plain prata, food was served in about 20 minutes, waiting times was abit long. Other than that, food was delicious and stall cleanliness was good.

Never disappoint you when you pick their Ma lah variant !
Foodie is fresh and yummy !

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: A no-frills but delicious and fresh meat Mookata place in a Toa Payoh kopitiam.  We realised that the meats were really fresh as they were not heavily marinated (to cover up using old meat) like some other places.  Loved the pork belly slices, the garlic pork collar and the streaky pork bacon.  However, the star of the show was their signature chilli sauce!  Would be great if this place could open until later as sometimes we love a good late night Mookata meal.

13/02/2022 sunday afternoon 2pm

The Axe is a new western stall in the area. Definitely better than the one in 409 hawker center! Must try! Cheaper, bigger quantity, friendly staff, and definitely more delicious!

I ordered the Mexicano grilled chicken for $7.90. The chicken skin is crispy and you can tell it is grilled slowly with care, hence the 10 minute waiting time. The mashed potato gravy has black pepper and tastes yummy. The aglio olio is okay but very large portion even when I ask them for less. I chose salad over fries, but the lettuce is chopped roughly anyhow with too sweet dressing. Overall, very big portion and hearty and enjoyable. Worth!

The mexicano version has a lot of raw onions and cheese, I think buying the normal grilled chicken for $6.90 is even better.

Also check out their buff ÊãõË¥¢Áå´ (lucky cat)!!!
Good service , fried rice and stir fried food is to go far

Unexpected gem! Each dish we ordered were yummy, and served super quickly too üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª

Ëæ£Â≠êÈ∏° was super crispy and flavourful! Cabbage fried rice sounded very normal but wow it was definitely a good plate of fried rice - recommend to try it! Everything else, like the lor mee, Xing hua bee hoon, Â•∂ÁôΩ were above average too~

only the fried yam and duck roll were slightly disappointing, because the amount of duck in there was pretty insignificant.

will definitely return!

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Ordered mutton, egg n vegetable. Taste delicious and price really reasonable. Best of all the service, everyone‚Äôs really friendly and patient when u order. Do come n try!

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
One of my best Teochew cuisine in Sg. (I‚Äôm a Teochew üòÖ) The roast piglet is pricy, but it‚Äôs so worth it.
Other than roast pork, the authentic fried kailan kway Teow and Yam Paste are not to be missed! We called it Âè§Êó©Âë≥„ÄÇÂÆûËá≥ÂêçÂΩí„ÄÇ
Pricy, but if you willing to part $$, a meal to you will not forget.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: Cheap and they have cheese masago sushi
Delicious ramen and rice chashu pork service 24hr good for everyone who live in night or day

Had the chai png today. While the 2 meats were good, the selection of vegetables was dismal.

The eatery is rather cramped up, so go during off-peak hours.

Would rate it as 3.5 stars.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Teh Tarik is nice. Kampung fried rice is nice. Nasi Goreng Pattaya is ok, but just a note, the fried rice is the lame type that got chopped carrots and peas. Service is decent.

(Translated by Google) Eat more

(Original)
Makan lagi

seriously big waste of time and money. also the WORSE hargao ive had in my life. cold and dry. ordered 2 pcs of meesua kueh and 2 pcs of hargao, and waited 20 mins! while my food sat at the counter turning cold! after i placed my order the cashier told me to wait outside the glass door and she would call me when my orders ready. the billboard which flashed the queue numbers never updated. i stood outside the shop for a GOOD 20 MINS AND GUESS WHAT? MY FOOD WAS LONG READY, SITTING AT THE INNER COUNTER, AND THE LADY NEVER NOTIFIED ME WHEN SHE SAID SHE WOULD. I GOT IMPATIENT AND ASKED WHERES MY FOOD, THEN THE LADY WHO PROMISED TO NOTIFY ME BUT DIDNT HANDED ME MY COLD FOOD. ALL THESE COULD BE PREVENTED IF THEY FIXED THEIR SYSTEM AND HAD BETTER CUSTOMER SERVICE!

closes at 10pm instead of 2am on friday..

prata's the soft kind instead of the crispy kind, but okok only

First visit. Lucky we made reservation beforehand as the place is small.
Food is very tasty and authentic! 3 person bill came to $48.60.
If you love variety then this is great as you get to try a lot as the portions are small.
Personally I like the wanton which is so smooth and its served in chicken soup. The chicken mushroom noodle and pan fried buns are fantastic along with the pumpkin pancake which is my partner's fav.  Not easily available elsewhere. Great way to end the meal.
XLB is the least of favourite as there is barely much filling or soup in it but it is still very very tasty.
For the price and quality of food, you‚Äôll find nothing else that compares in Singapore. They even have Jarritos. The staff is also great and make for a very positive experience.

The chicken and accompanying rice with its sauce and chilli are always consistently delicious. The meat is tender and the soy sauce that soaks it gives it that additional oomph. Service staff is efficient and cheerful. Notice they are older staff and hence more spontaneous in reacting to customers' requests.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
Great nasi lemak! The rice is fragrant and the chicken is tender and well grilled with a good smokiness to it. And WOAHHH the chilli has a great deal of kick and tastes really good!
Order: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang

Besides serving up one of the best claypot rice in Singapore, this location also has a large spread of other dishes that are of great quality! Calling in to make an EARLY BOOKING for your claypot is highly recommended to secure yourself a seat and reduce waiting time for food. Though I dare say that it is still worth the queue if you have to do so!

The chili sauces here are crazy spicy but go extremely well with the food.

Finding a lot for your vehicle will be the biggest challenge here. Good thing there is an underground carpark just opposite the restaurant.

Location is not so wheelchair friendly and will require some lifting. They might/should be able to assign tables closer to the entrance if a prior reservation call is made.

TMC was a surprise find for me and my wife. We were looking for a place to pass the time while waiting for our daughter to finish her dance class, and chanced upon this resto.

Food is really tasty. Coffee is really good. Staff is really friendly and customer-centric. Ambience is quiet and serene.

Bathrooms though were not too clean, so hoping that can be solved with periodic maintenance.

Will definitely revisit the place to try out their main dishes.

Had the Mee Rebus with satay - I think it's head to head with Rahim, albeit it has some interesting variation with the satay cut into the noodles, freshly cut red oninons and green/red chillis.  Also tried the Mee Soto/wing. Mee Soto was way above average. I personally prefer Rahim's mix of spice in the soup.
The original rasa sayang. Grew up eating this. All the staff are white haired and experienced. Good stuff cannot bluff
Wonderful food and great customer service

We ordered 4 different donburis (salmon, premium chirashi, bara chirashi and eel) for dinner. Each bowl was nicely presented. The bara chirashi got the most of the attention with its OTT garnishes. A   party in your mouth awaits if you like to mix everything up.

The price point for the bowls were above the average Japanese family restaurant but the quality and quantity of the seafood more than made up for it. I heard from the owner that fresh catch is flown in 2x a week from Japan. Worth a visit.

Just your average 24 Hour prata shop in the neighbourhood coffee shop. Nothing outstanding but it isn't terrible either. I don't actually recommend coming here for supper since they usually pre-prepare the pratas and leave them aside, so they aren't as fresh as you'd like. During day time is fine

Wanted to order from Devil's Kitchen but it was not yet open for business. So i walked a few more steps down and decided to order from this restaurant for a family dinner. It was nice as there was a 1 for 1 pizza / pasta offer.

Probably the first and last time I will order from this restuarant. Pizza base looked pre-made, ingredients are in generous quantity but the pizza looked like something you can simply whip up at home. Pasta was probably the only dish I might give a slight thumbs up for.

The ribeye was overdone. Salmon steak was also a miss (these mains comes with somd salad only, in case you were hoping there were fries as well)

Customer service though was a plus as there is this guy who would give out papadum to customers waiting for their orders.

I waited close to an hour for my order too. There was no proactive updates from the waiting staff as to the progress for my order (i waited in F&B before and this was something I did to my customers who had to experience long waiting times, and no one had to train me to do that, IMO its just common sense)

Their Power Mee Rebus is the King of Mee Rebus for me. Tangy gravy doused with peanut sauce and tongue-tingling green chillies (scoop aside if you can't take the heat) topped with a generous portion of kampung chicken. You will leave with a bulging belly and wide smile on your face. The portion is hearty even though it's just $4.50 (think it's $5 or $5.50 now as of July 2022). A must-try for at least once in your life
Nice Nices n good place for gathering.

Went there for my friend's birthday dinner.  The staff who took our order was quite friendly and introduced us a few popular dishes.
The stuffed chicken wings were ok, not something fantastic. Prawn cake was nice.. Green curry didn't seem appetizing to me but my friends enjoyed it. The mango sticky rice was good.. mango was sweet and rice was soft and warm.
I had lychee milkshake but it tasted more like blended lychee.. watery not nice.
We also ordered red ruby and something like cendol. The red ruby dessert had something that tasted like essence.  Don't recommend it.

We finished out dinner and sat there to chill and chat but the staff were eager to settle the bill and send us off.. they could tell us nicely that they are preparing to close for the day instead of throwing very obvious hints like mopping the floor.  :-/
The delivery is usually very slow. You need to wait at least for 2 hours to get your food delivered.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Service not that great. When asked for a glass of plain water, the first thing the waitress said is chargeable. We paid so much for the meal. It doesn't make sense if we can't afford for a glass of water. Need to train the staff how to communicate to customers.
Descent thai dishes, fresh ! Lemongrass drink is good !

If you want to try something other than XLB, check out @jinghuaxiaochi which specialises in different types of dumplings such as Steamed Vegetarian Dumplings ($8), Pan-fried Mixed Seafood & Pork Dumplings ($9) or the Rosemary & Cheese ‚Ä¶

1. There is hidden cost of service charge unless you pay with PayPal.

2. Ordered the yakibuta don and they served me a raw egg (totally regretted for not taking photo of it) - would have let the matter go instead of posting on social media if not for the unprofessional response from the staff - "our egg is like that one" after I pointed that the onsen egg was totally raw as the egg white was transparent.

3. Another staff changed the egg, came back still translucent (yes, a slight improvement I would say) - this time I took photos as attached. I'm sure anyone has a better understanding of onsen egg.

4. You might seriously want to consider another Japanese stall.. They use normal rice (not Japanese rice) and the rice was lumped together (see photo).

Went on a Sunday afternoon. This place is big enough to accomodate many people. Our order came quite fast despite the lunch crowd. I liked their mee goreng. Murtabak was good but was a bit burnt. We requested for nonspicy for the kiddos and the staff prepared yummy maggi goreng with hotdog. Noticed different races dining here too.
The staff is rude and doesn't understand English well. I won't visit again.

Extensive menu with wide variety of set meal options. Had the mentaiko salmon paired with sashimi salad set meal, comes with soup and chawamushi. Pretty filling. Service could be better, was seated at a corner and had a hard time getting the waiter/waitresses‚Äô attention.

First try and love the food n ambiance. Away from the crowd, reservations recommended to avoid disappointment! Tried the chicken burger and pork Ribs, simple meal yet delicious! Too bad no waffles today, will try next visit! Please get spare waffle machine as a backup can üòú
Good food at very reasonable prices and good service too. A recommended place to go for Your celebrations.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Pathetic biryani..  I dont why they priced it so high..

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Like dishes, staff friendly and attentive!

Just to share experience. This evening on 25 Dec 2019. We ordered take away rojak for $26/-. We asked for onion, green chilli and cucumber. When reaching home we opened up the packet and found out the man gave one slice of onion and cucumber each and one green chilli besides the rojak we ordered. It was good lesson for me. Next time pls check first before leaving.
They maintain their sambal taste
Go to place for the duck. Price is not cheap, but for the quality and service, it is not too bad!
Fish and soup is nice. But... The papaya salad really can not make it. Lack of so many ingredients and the taste is very salty.

Basically, a Starbucks concept in hawker center but added on with Thai drinks such as coconut Thai milktea, rose tea and butterfly pea and half price compared to cafes! They uses espresso machine to extract their tea, a method called teapresso adapted from UK. Hopefully this will get recognize to bring our local hawker culture to a whole new level, all the best to them! üí™üèª

We first patronised their stall back when they were at Katong Student Hostel. Visited them again when they moved to Clementi. Now they have moved to Balestier and it's the third time we have looked for them. Now this says something about their food. My absolute favourite dish is the honey chicken, you can ask for the rice version too. Their Phad Thai, mostly different from others with their signature wet style with tomato based sauce is worth mentioning too. This is unusual from most Thai food places.

Located in B2 of AMK Hub where Fairprice is, just beside the Dessert shop.
Bought voucher from ShopBack. Service was ok and prompt, waiting time was okay.
But food is subpar. Ordered curry chicken katsu and gyu don.
Look at the gyu don rice that looks like mui fan or porridge. Totally wet from the sauce which is not to my preference. Note: I didn't mix the rice btw. I'm not sure if donburis are supposed to be this wet. Beef was average, not too chewy. Red ginger not sweet enough.
Not sure if it's just an outlet problem, but I might reconsider getting mains from here next time. Sushi for quick fixes are still average and sufficient.

Today is 3rd May, 2022. We have tried this restaurant many times since we live in the condo upstairs Jurong Point. the food is ok, but the staff's attitude is not acceptable.
We were standing at the queuing line, a Staff called Catherine, walking towards us without saying anything and didn't even look at us. She stand at the welcoming counter and doing something at the counter, just half a meter away from us, very close, trying to ignore our "hi", "hello" and many louder sentences because we wanted to get her attention, we even waved our hands a lot.
We could not believe this bad behavior from a staff of such a well-known restaurant.
We would like to highlight the female staff- Catherine to be trained properly, otherwise we will escalate to the management or will never return to this restaurant again!!!
No Test..No Clean...No Test Food..

I'm a frequent diner here with colleagues and the taste never disappointed. They have affordable lunch specials such as basil pork rice set at $6.80 and salted egg fried rice at $5.50. The portion is big and we usually share the fried rice among 3 girls.

Their homemade tofu and garlic chicken are amazing, must order for group lunches.

The owners are very friendly too! :)
Amazingly delicious food. I recommend the Carbonara. Personally, i add an extra grilled fish to go with it too. Thumbs up!
The porridge is salted and the portion of the dish is very small. Especially for butter garlic lala, think only have less than 15pcs, and its not worth it.
The opening hours are not correct. Please correct it is wasting valuable morning office time. I came at 8.45 am and it was closed.
The boss is friendly. After so many years patronising this place he is like a friend.  All the food is good. My favourite is the roti prata delicious. üëçüëçüëçüëçüëç
I give you best combi from this place. must try SINAR's tomyam soup with salted fish fried rice, super tasty
great food, great ambience, staff were friendly as always!

The Deep fried prawn ball with pumpkin and butter sauce was the best and most yummy dish! I‚Äôm still missing it ü•≤

Pork belly meat was tender and soft too.

Overall value for money as all the dishes we ordered were delicious. The meal was made even better as we ordered deep fried baby squid which is uncommonly found these days at Zi char places, a dish we rarely get to eat.

Will be back for more! üëçüèª
Seller was in her own world, we ordered a chicken masalla, she gave the last piece to an indian lady that came 20mins after us. It is a racist spot, be careful
The japanese bento is good n price is cheap.Good value for money.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Alot of choice to choose for nasi padang. Very long queue during lunch time.

Price wise abut expensive, but worth it as the food is very good.
Love the duck.. Worth the money. Service is good but price a bit high.

Decent place for yunnan ËøáÊ°•Á±≥Á∫ø. Customised my own with pork broth, rice noodles, 4 vegetables and one meat for $7.20. The broth was really good but I felt the rice noodles could have been better and the portion of the ingredients could have been more generous. Service was prompt and there was just enough seats to hold the lunch crowd.
Very very good for the price. Will be back again and again

Best valued Nasi Lemak in Sg !
Only $4.50 for a generously portioned set that comes with 2 freshly fried chk wings ! A favourite haunt for my weekly visits to the area.
Ordered a $12 sirloin steak medium doneness. Super overcooked and hard to chew. Not worth buying.
Old school Japanese home cook feel. I've been having their curry rice for the past 20 odd years. Their grilled salmon taste great too..!!
So. Freaking. Good. Chicken masala, butter chicken, and I forgot what else, all of them tasted great. Love the garlic naan too. Hands down one of the best indian food I've tried in Singapore.

I see the comments are positive, but I don't think so!
Bad attitude of the staff!
I ordered with extra noodles, but the staff forgot to add noodles for me, So I went to Ramen Station ask for extra noodles with the staff, When I asked the staff,he was quite , when I asked again he threw the noodles in front of me!
Felt like I owed him money or killed his family!!!üò°üò°
Restaurant was very small , All is self collect self service .
Food was normal,but is cheaper.

They should be that I have rated them one of the worst Japanese Izakaya in Singapore. It seems that the chef is not really focus in his cooking and rushing through just to get the food cook and done with any details. Bland taste and poor customer service. BANNED!

Delicious Ipoh food. The curry mee was super delicious. Thick and flavorful. The assam laksa was authentic too! The ice white coffee was thick and good. Anson special chee cheong fun was special. It was full house at 6.30 pm on a Sunday. Ample parking space outside the cafe. Bought some Ipoh snacks to try.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: The dishes we ordered were good esp the duck and chili crab. They also had a good selection of wine. The service staff was fantastic. Will definitely make another visit there.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Very good service. Staff were efficient and kind when serving. Food was delicious too

Always love a Sunday dinner at this neighbourhood steakhouse ü•© service is hit & miss depending on who‚Äôs serving you (I had a pleasant experience this visit, less the last). Most importantly food is good, so I‚Äôll be back!

i feel so shock when i reach home and open up the box, portion is so little and also i ask the guy packing the last piece of chicken is the chicken hot and he mention  "yes hot hot" and he pack inside the plastic bag and turns out chicken is so cold just like it have been left in the food tray for few hour.

Nice and simple breakfast!
Seems like ONLY on Tuesday - they serve chickpeas

Super friendly, patient. Though queue was long, approx 10 pax when I was there at 11.10, they served fast and efficient.

Sorry the photo not good enough to show the stall. But the q was long. Only nasi lemak. No other dishes.

A hidden gem in the neighbourhood! Considering the quality of the food we get at the prices, it's very reasonable and worthwhile. Get the mac & cheese for sides - unlike the usual, obviously microwaved packed ones you eat at other western places, this will not leave you with regrets! The home cured bacon thicks were so good too, we came back for more!

Pork chops were tender so it wasn't hard for my grandma to chew on, and I enjoyed the cordon bleu as well :) if you have some more space for the pulled pork quesadillas, I recommend you getting a portion! We got them to go and had them for supper, still good!

Plus point: they're pets friendly (as long as you're sitting outdoors)! It's better to call in to inform the staff if you're bringing a pet, so they can keep the tables outside for you :)

The hightea buffet is worth checking in. All
the food items are very tasty and couldn‚Äôt find any flaws to it. The dumplings with chilli & oil are exceptionally good! They have frozen ones available to purchase too.
Acceptable. Nothing great to shout about

Green tea was not hot enough, sushi rice is overcooked and marshy, chawamushi with roe the roe is not fresh, gyoza tasted doubled fried and sitting in a place of sweet sauce. There are also fruit flies around. Never will visit again.

Was looking for a TingKat meal for the family during the CV19 period and was recommended this place. Was informed that they had to convert to TongKat business due to the CV19 and I‚Äôm glad that they did. Coz it allowed my family and I to have a taste of their home cook style food. Also... might I add that there‚Äôs a standard to their cooking. Unlike mass cooked food caterers, you can see the effort and pride put into preparing the food.

Received the first delivery today and am really impressed. Rice was well cooked. Not too hard nor soft. Braised fish was fresh and not too spicy or salty. Mushrooms are not the el cheapo type of mushrooms. Soup was yummy and flavorful too.

Over all... they are not the cheapest in the market but comparing the food quality and that the food is delivered hot... it‚Äôs definitely worth every cent. Portions are generous too. My family are quite heavy eaters and are all quite stuffed after lunch.

Was so impressed that am going to change the 10 days trial to prob the 20 days menu.

A cozy little restaurant along Thomson! The price is pretty affordable for all items on the menu itself! It also has a very homely feel to the restaurant itself which sets it apart from other Japanese restaurants you find outside! Food is good too! Recommended!

Not my first time here, I had always been impressed with their menu... Today is my first try of their ÈæôËôé‰ºö Crab with Seafood In Claypot. This is not ordinary curry or laksa crab, it's the most innovative Crab Beehoon I have ever tried... It has the savoury seafood umami, don't be surprised to find salted fish and Chinese herb dang gui in it, amazing cocoction, super fresh & firm crab meat üëçüëçüëç. Must try!

Another good jajangmyeon option. We tried their seafood fried jajangmyeon. It's oilier as compared to the usual jajangmyeon as there is chilli oil in it but its more fragrant than the usual jajangmyeon. Not the best but worth a try. We like their spicy garlic fried chicken. Delicious üòã üòã üòã  as its full of onion, garlic and chilli. Mukjja is definitely a korean Chinese restaurant worth a try.

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Money worth it. Can add on more side with reasonable price. 5-11pm so better make a reservation if not long waiting list Esp weekend. 2 choices of sauces are match with soup and BBQ. Must try if you are the Mookata lovers.
Aircon zichar inside grains & hops. Contact number 69171659.

Been around for years now, the go to for many looking for Indian cuisine.

‚è∞ they have a signage stating it will take 20-30 minutes during peak hours, and we gotten our food 10 minutes in at around 7pm on a weekend

Food was good, prata was fluffy the way I like, with a tinge of crispness at different bits - curry was generous too, spicy enough but not too overpowering or powdery.

Definitely use the $0.50 vouchers from shopee to enjoy better value off your meal! üëçüèª

I‚Äôve ordered a normal Phad Thai, which co gains fish and prawn. Considering the ingredient used, it‚Äôs very generous to its price of $6. By comparison, it‚Äôs far value for money and tasting to other Thai chain outlet present in Singapore. It would continue visiting.

The crowd has return is full house tonight.Anyway we do a booking earlier.Tonight we have orders coffee spare ribs, the meat was very tender, garlic vegetables with oyster sauce,minced meat with dip fried tofu,bitter gourd stir fried with pork ribs in blackbeam sauce,the ribs was  very soft and Indonesian stir fried chicken with sauce not really spicy.
Very nice selection of food and hot drinks

Very pleasant experience. I frequent their flag ship outlet at Jalan Besar area when they were still those old run down dim sum place.
Now they are closer to me at Amk, I love their mee suah kueh. Always my favourite. Their banana prawn is awesome too. Yam paste with ginkgo nuts is good too.

Really nothing to complain about. It‚Äôs very very tasty. Their set menu is very affordable too !

Good job Swee Choon! But if possible to move inside the mall it‚Äôs even better so can queue and wait in aircon area.

@steakgrillsg is a cosy restaurant that serve delicious and affordable cuisine.üòãüòä

Let's see what we have here:

1. Quest fries S$9
Crispy fries served with in house cheese sauce, chicken and bacon bits.
Their fries is really good esp with the cheese sauce. üòã their fries is crispy and fragrant. Must order. üëç
,.
2. Home cures bacon thicks
Thick cut belly strips that had been cured for days, smoked and then grilled
This is flavorful,best for people who like pork with more fats. I personally prefer their pork chops instead.

2. St Louis Rib 1/3 S$16
Applewood smoked ribs served with in house sauce
This ribs is tender with some fats and lean mix. Portion is so value for $.
,.
3.Ribeye 250g S$21
All time favorite with a good balance of fat and lean
( I don't eat beef, but my foodie friends like this)
,.
4.Prawn Arribiata S$15
With chilli, prawns and pomodoro. I like the pasta noodles it is spicy and tasty. I could finish the whole plate myself. üòãThe prawn could be better though.
,.
5. Truffle Pork Chop S$16
Pork tenderloin grilled and topped with truffle cream sauce
I personally like this very much without dipping the sauce. It is lean meat yet not tough, very nicely marinated. I strongly recommend to order this üòã love this.üëç

Review posted on my IG: Yummymich
Great Grilled Japanese food with reasonable price tag.

Taste: love it!
Esp. the tofu is really nice!! Soft and smooth and tasty

Vegetarian options available

Interesting cafe with cosy setting, serving both Nepalese and Western. Rice is very fragrant, meat is herby but rather dry. Western dishes are average, portion is quite large though. Good when you want to try something different.

One restaurant is at the end of the block. It is worth waiting (not many seats). The Heng Hua rice noodle (Bee Hoon) is a must-try; although this is on the dry side, you have a different sensory while having it. Must try the blood cockles, which is now seldom available. The braised pork leg is the highlight of the meal; however, beware of the fats. The sweet and sour fish is also quite interesting, although deep-fried, it's so well done that you might want to go back to get more. Wear light clothing it's warm eating there.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Very nice carrot cake. It have a nice tempura texture to it. The chilli is like those Thai Sweet chilli. Super enjoyable however watch those calories. The hawker mix a lot of oil into the carrot cake and egg mixture before frying. Hence the carrot cake is very fragrant.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Came here to grab a bite and it turn out to be a feast. I enjoyed the saut√©ed Colourful vegetable assortment which is nice and crunchy. The crispy beancurd sheet wrapped with assorted mushroom is well prepared. The braised Dong Po Pork Belly with lotus bun is worth a try - it‚Äôs nice and tender and almost melts in your mouth. The saut√©ed Shanghai rice flour cake is average but the rice flour definitely is light on the bite which is rare to come by. This place is hidden from the main view so you need look out as you walk by.
Must try the truffle beef don, it's delicious!

Having bad dining experience with this restaurant, the soup is super duper salty like drinking msg and the drinks was too sweet. This is my first time to leave my review on google, to me food Costly and tasteless! Will not go back again‚òπÔ∏è. If really want to say, the service provided still okay.

Heard of this shop from reviews by some friends and decided to check it out. First feel is that the shop is really old school and authentic.

We chose the 4 pax package. The hakka noodles and suan pan zi felt like it was pre cooked, instead of cooked fresh. The taste of the hakka noodles were abit disappointing in the sense that it was to the blender side. However, this might be because the other dishes are saltier and the noodles might be meant to be eaten with the other dishes.

The yong tau foo is really nth to shout out about. Average at best.

The Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ was towards the saltier side, but I really like the flavor. I would have given a higher rating if the pork was more tender. But some people like it that way. The chicken was nicely done.

Their chillis are a must try for those who are in for a kick and it really blends well with all the dishes.

Staff was courteous, efficient, and nice. One thing I really liked was that this restaurant serves Chinese tea or warm water foc. Which is so hard to find nowadays and something I really appreciate.

Overall, price was very decent and it is a nice establishment to support and visit. All da best to their business.
Nice location and with a great view.  Not many options of beer on tap -  they only have archipelago lager and summer ipa. The salad is quite popular.

The chicken rice that they are famous for is still pretty much the staple for this outfit, although they do serve up other complementary options as well. However, the food quality seems to have dipped somewhat since years ago, and many of the food items were slightly too salty (especially the roasted chicken).
Solid indian/malay/chinese food  . If they put their place in delivery apps im sure there will be more orders than they have currently üëçüèΩ

Food was good. Service was not, their server was giving attitude problems and they did not have a clear system in counting the alcohol. Issue was solved in the end but overall there were many unpleasant moments with the service given.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Worst gril working there, she so rude when i walk off  and ordered at neighbour shami restaurant. The girl walk there and talking to shami staff about me. Worst service.
The dumplings are just the right amount of thickness and the soup is good. Recommended to try this, especially if you have been to Shanghai before and are craving the authentic dumplings there

Aside from the delicious food, the staff are nice and approachable with smiles.
Sirloin Set is good and the Cheese Chicken with Sausage Set is hefty in quantity

Its our first time at yr resturant. Thk u for the friendly service. The curries are not too spicy n came piping hot which we love. Thumbup for free flow papadam. It will be perfect if the condition could keep us cool during mealtime. We are perspiringüòÖ.

We will definitely be back for more catchup meals wuth friends n family.

Keep up your good food n thk u so muchü•≥ü•≥ü•≥
Not bad

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Air-condition restaurant. Place is clean and new, floor abit slippery but okay. The waiter are kinda attentive, even though they are very busy. If you having a la cart meal, do check if the servings are correct, they might missed one or two. Overall experience is good.
Tried the signature curry chicken with bread. Yummy.. the lemongrass drink is too sweet though.

For an experience not bad. Quite a number of sushi varieties to choose from. The Hamachi sashimi is a big disappointment, not fresh at all with the 4 pcs for $5+. Wonder why they serve unfresh sashimi in the first place to spoilt their branding.
And for $25 for 1 pax not a cheap option, didn't even order a lot of things.
Ok for 1st time experience, not really a regular goto place.

@ichikokudosg LOOKS promising.

They have quite extensive menu and are halal certified therefore their broth are simmered with chicken bone instead. Here their ramen noodle is using hokkaido wheat flour which menu stated thin noodle for most of their ramen except the spicy version.

Moving on to what we have.
Ichikokudo Ramen Original. Is Shoyu Ramen which we feel it taste just plain SALTY üòÜ. I personally didn't like the egg as well. Doesn't have the molten centered yolk.

Tomato Ramen with Cheese, felt the broth is too thick and overwhelming upon first spoon.
