Like thickened tomato sauce / tomato puree with some fresh diced tomatoes while it does have that tanginess BUT couldn‚Äôt detect any cheese at all and everything just taste VERY SALTY and jelat. Unfortunately, we had to surrender the entire bowl.

Guess we just can't appreciate shoyu base ramen and chicken broth. üòù

Ig: @zoey_belle_
Good Japanese food at a hawker centre! Their signature salmon set gives u a large piece of salmon fillet and love the tempura there!

Good point is that meat is tender. However, taste-wise is just okok. Perhaps because the chicken chop is marinated more salty, the spaghetti was made diluted and bland (to the extent that the flour taste from pasta was so obvious and the spaghetti tasted amateurish though texture was al Dante). Auntie was also very irritated when I tried to ask if they had alternatives to tomato base... For $7.30, it did not feel worth nor did the portion make up for it.

my favorite curry puffs in singapore! love love the batter. i love the mushroom puffs more (because im not a curry fan). also they recently have kaya puffs, which are amazing!! there is this sesami green bean fried ball that i like too. this one is right next to old curry times. their menu is slightly more varied than other old chang kees.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Nice Thai food but price abit expensive and small portion or else it be a 5 stars

A strange place for a good eatery to be for sure! ü§î Nestled in Science Centre, next to Kids Stop. üòÇ The naan was legit possibly the best I‚Äôve tried! Soft, fluffy, crispy on the edges. ü•∞ Tried fish tikka, chicken tikka, butter chicken and palak paneer and all were fantastic as well! Prices came up to $88 for our table of 5+2 which was very reasonable!

Lovely Malaysian fare which is pretty much as authentic as it gets! Their Assam Laksa is definitely worth eating, and comes with generous amounts of toppings.

Apart from Assam Laksa, do try their Char Kway Teow, Curry Yong Tau Foo Char Kway Teow and Claypot Rice. It‚Äôs really quite authentic and bound to hit your cravings for Malaysian food in the right spots!
Good south Indian food

We went for a Sunday Brunch at Tanoke. The food was a delight especially the 3-cut Wagyu platter. We ordered medium-rare and each cut of the wagyu meat melts in your mouthüòã I love the ambience of the place as well as the design and the lights. The service is splendid and friendly . Overall experience was excellent and we enjoyed it muchüëçüëç

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Went twice so far. The service really sucked. They are also severely short-handed - only 2 person running the whole place. Tried their buffet on our second visit and was told that every dish could only be ordered once. Okay...so we made our order, and was then told we cannot order the same type of meat twice? Excuse me? üò° Their definition of ‚Äúbuffet‚Äù is ridiculous, and the buffet price is unreasonable with this kind of funny limitation...In the end we had to order something else, which was not delicious at all. Yucks...

Ordered via Bungkus. All food is horrible! Except for Tom Yum! Blackpepper beef too oily! Crab fried rice failed! Just plain rice mix with soy sauce and add crab meat on the top. Fork & spoon crab fried rice more nice. Kailan also can't accept! Basil just a spoonful and throw in a bin. Not worth it. Gonna be my 1st & the last. All food gone to the waste except for tom yum. Waste money!
Excellent food and very reasonable price

We tried Ribeye steak and some other dishes. Yes, the taste is really splendid. Atmosphere is relaxing, pricing is not too expensive too. Service team is awesome, always trying their best to serve their customers.

This is overall my family's favourite Soup Restaurant outlet. Taste and quality of the dishes are consistently good, and the restaurant managers Bobo and Joanna Choong are always warm, friendly, attentive and accommodating. Their service is top-notched. Highly recommended for a cosy delicious family meal.

The duck rice is not nice and is very expensive. $6 per plate just only a few pieces of meat on it.
I go other place eat duck drumsticks is only $5.5.

Came for a birthday celebration. This place brings back all the memories.
Set lunches are value for money.
Love the mushroom soup and garlic bread which were the mainstays since many many years ago
Had the chicken and steak which came on a sizzling plate w baked potato and long beans as sides.
Baked potato was delish w the sour cream , bacon condiments
Quite a long wait for the food. Seem a little short handed and the service staff seem flustered. All items were delicious though!

Had our dinner here.
Hard copy menu price was outdated, so scan QR Code can see the latest price.

Crowded during dinner time, but staffs working efficiency, fast action to sort out the seat for us.

Table arrangement quite close to each other, so perhaps is good place to eat but not stay long.

We ordered some simple dishes, overall all taste are nice and yummy.

Personally feel the mango sticky rice little pricy.
Nice food and one of the outlet with fast queue turnaround.
They serve mee soto, soto ayam, mee rebus, gado gado with choices of add on & satay. All are delicious. For takeaways, soup & gravy are packed separately so the noodle & ketupat don't get soggy üëç

Over priced. Charged 6.40 sgd for one curry drumstick (no potatoes, would have to add money if asked for potatoes that were in the same food tray) and quail eggs (five of them).

No rice.
Not crowded. Nice place to enjoy the yummy KFC chicken üêî
One of the best hawker ramen. The mushroom plate is comparable to expensive japanese restaurants even though its half the price
Rare find especially in a neighbourhood setting for a good steak üòã love the garlic butter merlot sauce! Would definitely be back!

This outlet is at the old North wing, near Cold storage. We had the tandoori set for two and used an eatigo discount for 20% at 6.30pm (only at Northpoint outlet) $25.60 for two of us plus two teh tarik. Impatient diners must note it does take some time for tandoori. It was a very good deal because the set was huge and most importantly, the quality was good. Chicken was well flavoured and tender. You queue, pay and collect your drinks. The buzzer system is a little odd. They ring you once but it is actually for the drinks which you have already collected. The second buzzer is the one which would indicate your food is ready. Good service at this outlet. Having said that, I am quite a patient and forgiving person.

Went there last Sunday but it was super crowded and it didn't look like there was a system to manage the crowd. There were people standing around the tables to wait/chope the tables. There were people queuing to order the food. You wouldn't know what to do, whether to find a table first or to queue and place order at the cashier. Just very messy. We immediately left the place and the group behind us pretty well did the same.

Went there again ytd, a Friday afternoon. Around 2pm plus which was already after lunchtime. Only a few tables were occupied but there were at least 3 to 4 tables with crockery uncleared. There was only one uncle trying to clear all the dirty tables and the used crockery after being cleared was placed beside the self service station for the clean crockery. The hygiene level, IMHO, was totally not there. The menu at the cashier was also stained w gravy and they didn't even bother to wipe it.

We ordered curry chicken noodles, assam laksa, two fried chicken. Assam laksa was quite good, the flavour was there and as close as those I had in JB. Curry noodles on the other hand was lacklustre, and the chicken pieces were probably 4 thin slices. The fried chicken was my least favourite, one dimension flavour tho it was served hot.

0 frills "steak" restaurant...

Prices in generally are reasonable, but I felt that it was a tad overpriced for the quality of meat served.

I'd still come back cause its the local steak spot when I'm craving some beef...
$39.80++ (min 3 pax) for the Ala-Carte Buffet, you can eat till you drop, but quality wise it is just average, noting to Woh or Wah about it.

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: I didn't get the name of the lady who was fronting customers at cashier. But I wanted give kudos for her patient and customer-oriented service. Other than Fiery Chicken, there were no other chickens available. Also no fish no that. I wonder how Astons Toa Payoh do business. But the lady kept running in and out, in to take order, while out to inform customers in queue the unavailable items. I would give all my 5 stars to the lady but none to the branch manager.
For $1, you can get a plate of Nasi lemak. I think this is enough to describe the value for money meal you can get at this place!
Extremely nice and delicious western food. Prepared and cooked with charcoal caused the taste nice and something different. Price is reasonable and the food portion quite big.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
Nov 2020. Another birthday celebration leveraging on JUMBO's J$. Teochew cuisine had always been one of my favourite Chinese culinary dominations. Ordered Pomfret, Tofu in Crab meat, Pig Trotter Terrine etc.
The staff were cold though.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Bad experience. Suppose to be the pioneering  branch yet the service was terrible.The serving staff questioned me on the number of packets of red chilli that I need  when I ordered  3 packets of  food and requested me to take just one packet instead of 3 packets. Gosh, who was the customer in the first place? I had  been to other branches ie. Holland Drive, Bukit Merah, Jalan Sultan and Clementi (the best so far) and they did not disappoint me. As for the Balestier branch, kind of disappointed with their attitude, and it seemed like they did not improve as I read from other reviews sharing about the staff attitude. Hence they really need to buck up.The food and dishes though were good and consistent with the others branches.

A surprise find. Decided to give them a try while walking past the shops at Toa Payoh. Wasn't disappointed, in fact I was quite blown away by their dishes.

This is also one of the few places I know that serve abacus seeds, which are quite hard to find; they did a fantastic job of it too.

Will definitely go back, even if it's just for the abacus seeds

My fourth visit to this outlet. The restaurant still managed to uphold its standard from the day of its opening. Polite and friendly staff and most importantly the food is 10/10. I couldn't have asked for more. Will definitely come for the fifth time :)

I have been a customer at the Jurong West coffeeshop and moved to Yishun now. I really liked their Thai wings, sweet & sour fish, fried rice and kung po chicken at Jurong West. At Yishun I really like their Tom Yum seafood soup, Mee Goreng seafood, Thai style chicken (it's all about the sauce) and  prawn paste chicken! Looking forward to trying more dishes! Really tasty food!

Tims Restaurant & Caf√© is one of the nicest neighborhood eatery to dine at. With a wide variety of unique menu items, ranging from Western to Nepalese cuisine, it's never a dull moment when eating here.
Their Christmas Special menu is extremely delicious and well prepared, early orders are a must! One of the very few affordable places that serves their turkey succulent enough to wipe away your fear of dry turkey. (Not yet released but you can pre-order takeaway for Christmas dining in the comfort of your home.)
Super friendly Lady seller whom I knew for at least 20 years. 1 of the best I have eaten and their fragrance Pandan rice stood out for me. Price is super economical.Must try if you haven't.

Come here for a quintessential Malay breakfast! Mee Rebus and Lontong were available when we got here at 10am on a Thu. Lontong was good and decent and the Mee Rebus was definitely above-average. Worth a try! This place is hidden find indeed!

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
13 Dish | 50+ bucks

3rd visit

Quality is dropping with every visit...started out really good that we went for twice consecutive weekend.

However it's still really crowded with the another wanton stor holding the fort. Hence expect to wait for 20 min or more if you have a group of 4 and more.

Overall it's still offer affordable price for a neighbourhood dimsum

This stall has been Ard for many years. When I pass by AMK I will head down here for their Penang prawn noodle. The dry version is my favorite accompanied by the rich tasting prawn noodle soup. No this is not those typical prawn noodle store.This is Penang style prawn noodle!
Good food, but service standard could be improved. Should also consider introducing membership benefits for customers.
Value for money $1 per stick but must wait a bit for the food to serve

Had it on a weekday for dinner at 530pm. The long beans was very very cold and had a slight sour taste, signs of the food being prepared and left there for a long time. Blatant disregard of food safety. Ordered Ayam Merah and what arrived was similar to curry chicken, both taste and appearance wise. Was told that this is their version of Ayam Merah......is this a joke? That is totally curry chicken. The other stir fried veggie tasted horrible too but at least it was slightly warm. Two plates cost us $13++

The curry is very tasty, and healthy (no coconut milk!). The dry laksa is tasty and fragrant. The salmon otak is unique and good quality. Chicken curry hor fun is very well made too, with a lot of ingredients - fish cake, chicken, tau pok, tau gay, hard boiled egg, okra...
Was also pleasantly surprised that their hot chrysanthemum tea is brewed with real chrysanthemum and served in quite a large mug, and not too sweet.

The ingredients are freshly prepared, all are warm when served. Love the fish, is fresh, not overly fried, outside is crispy n inside is soft n warm. The sambal chilli is not hot, taste is different from the usual sambal

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
I have so many good things to say about this place. Went there for ala carte buffet dinner with my family of 4. To be honest, we did not have high hopes and we were not expecting us to order more than 2 rounds of food. But each dish that came, we finished it immediately. Portion size was just nice for 4 of us. We ended up ordering 4 rounds of food, a total of 11 or 12 dishes excluding desserts!! Durian sticky rice is a MUST order!!

All in all, the food here way surpassed our expectations. The chefs cook the dishes upon ordering. Will definitely recommend all to dine in here at least once.

Only thing is that the location is quite a ‚Äúbirds dont lay eggs place‚Äù üòÜ

The food and service are good!

The owner prioritises the customers‚Äô needs. For instance, we ordered an extra bowl of rice and the owner said to finish our food first and there‚Äôs no rush to pay. It‚Äôs really small actions like this that elevates the entire service level!

We tried the batang fish steamboat, marmite Chicken, furong omelette, minced meat tofu! All of the dishes are super nice! The prices are reasonable too!

Strongly recommend!
Lousy service as in i order a set and there is no rice... have to talk to 2 staffs then the rice came. Order wagyu not bad but the meat is too thin slice.... not really worth to go.

Very tasty steamboat, piping hot and rich. Staff keep filling soup. Fish is gd quality.

Jan 21 - 2nd visit. teochew fish porridge is excellent. $6 1 pot. See picture below. die die must try

April 4 - 3rd visit. Fish porridge standard maintained. The ÈüÆËèúÈ•∫ skin very thin, prawn very fresh
If you looking for Lok Lok taste Same like JB then you must try this restaurant‚Ä¶ especially the oil fried mushrooms ‚Ä¶ and their Satay sauce is the best to eat with anything ‚Ä¶

Been there for lunch on Saturday at around 1.30 pm and the place had enough seating available. All of the food that we ordered was good. The satti sorru is actually good enough for 2 people. The mutton pepper was the highlight with an amazing thick gravy and soft meat. The chicken and the prawn in the satti sorru was pretty tasty. The seabass masala was just deep fried seabass with an extra coating of some masala. It might look spicy but it's just right and not too overpowering. All of that with a couple of butter milk and a coconut cost us SGD 82.
Neighbourhood Thai cuisine at average price. Food is proportionate average with no surprise.

Decided to come over for dinner on the 13th November 2021.

This outlet has a house rule that doesn‚Äôt allow more than 2 person to a table, which wasn‚Äôt clearly communicated (only an a4 advisory inside the eating area itself).

It wasn‚Äôt communicated to us while we were placing our order and only after paying for our food. Me, my wife and my baby in hand were at the counter ordering our food and I felt they had every opportunity to tell us then, not only after we have paid for our food and taken out seat.

I can respect that a restaurant can have their own house rule. I am extremely upset that it wasn‚Äôt communicated clearly. We ordered something that was clearly for sharing and we have been greatly inconvenienced.

We would have gone to eat somewhere else if it was communicated to us clearly.

Great and affordable Thai food. My favourites are the tomyum soup, basil chicken, tod man pla, tang hoon and pad thai. Highly recommended. You can call in to order as well and they will tell you what time to go to pick up the food. The belacan is out of this world and goes well with seafood.
Great portion of ingredients at affordable prices. I will definitely go back again!! They have fish skin on their menu which was sooo good!! The service was excellent as well üëç
Good food. Especially the prata and thosai. Cleanliness can be improved

Wah I tell you, the owner of the stall damn smart. It was a hot day and i was sweating like mad so i needed a desert to cool me down. The owner instantly introduce me to the coconut jelly before i could read his menu. I tried the 1st one and got a 2nd one immediately. Haven't had a jelly desert this good in a long time. Will definitely come back for more. THANK YOU!! ü•∞

A hidden Thai food gem in a HDB heartland. Atmosphere is quite realistic.

Food portions on the small side, but enables a group to order more variety.

Taste wise is not too bad, can visit again.

One of the better Chinese vegetarian restaurant. Personal favourites are the peking duck and sambal petai.

Waitresses are super attentive. Food and ambience is very good. However, some dishes can be quite pricey.

Super crowded on the weekend and difficult to find a seat but the kway chap is super worth it.

There were a lot more stalls I would love to try again, especially the chicken clay pot rice, the congee and some of the more traditional offerings.

Kway Chap and Braised Duck stall are both gone now.

Waited my order for 10mins over the counter, my number was called but the crew have no idea where was my order. I ordered to eat in, but they packed it up. So i had to wait for then to find it and put it on the tray....   Had breakfast muffin and wrap each time and the egg has shell... Big breakfast was unavailable on the saturday and have limited options... bad

We ordered the prosperity set menu for our reunion dinner.
Food is prepared rather fast and ingredients are fresh.
We have a satisfactory meal as all the dishes are palatable and tasty.
We definitely be back for more meals in the near future.
Good atmosphere, good quality of food. You pay for what you get. üëç
soup tasted v good but soba tastes like strings with flour.

restaurant name: Tian Yuan Xiang (United Square) - Chicken Essence for Pregnancy in SG
content: it's really good and tastes just like chicken essence. convenient to heat up and consume

Penang food at afforadable prices. There r aircon seats inside. Staff are friendly. The laksa & char kway teow are not bad. The kangkong is a bit too sweet. The chendol has gula melaka taste & the green strands doesnt taste plasticky.

Yummy!!!
We ordered Half a roast chicken, Spinach with 3 eggs, Fried Prawn Roll, Claypot chicken liver and Sliced Fish with Ginger. All for only $87!
Ample of parking space and if you are coming here on a weekend, do call in to reserve first! :)

Your money is better spent at Genki. Decent quality but a lot more rice:topping ratio.

Makes up for it with speedy service.

Attended a wedding there. It was intimate & cosy. Though only comment for improvement would be to check the quality of the food as we were served seafood (prawns & lobster) which I personally felt was not too fresh. Other than that staff did well to host everyone, check on all tables & ensure we were well fed. Thanks for the experience!

The ‚ÄúS-11‚Äù western food is finally back! Glad to see the entire family back in the stall as we have been patronizing this stall since my secondary school days.
Try the chicken cutlet. It‚Äôs so soft and nice! Hope to see fried rice back on the menu.

Very friendly staff that bring double joy to the great meal served.
Ingredients in the Nasi Lemak bring simple, but true in every ways.
Chicken Merah set meal is saucy with a pinch of hidden sweetness that lightens your taste buds.

Staffs attitude is very very bad ! I think she need to send back for training! Hope the management can take action for this branch ! This not 1 or 2 times like this services !!!!!!!!!!! Bad !!!!!!!!! Not recommended coming !!!!!!!!
Own self check in without temperature scanning. Food not tasty anymore. My prawn noodle has a weird smell for the pork slices.

Decent nasi lemak served with green fragrant rice. Coconut taste is present in the rice, chilli is not overpowering and ikan bilis complements the dish quite well. Fried chicken wing was not too tough nor soggy. $3.50 is also a decent price for the meal, which is slightly above standard to those nasi lemak stalls going for $2.50-$3.
Good mince meat noodle, haha Yong tow hu
This stall serves the closest to Penang Prawn Noodles. Lady boss very friendly and soup is superb!!!
Do not order when lots of people is lining especially on Sunday. The front counter 's work slowly. Have to wait for a super long time.

Not an honest hawker. Ordered 2 packets of Fish & Chips. 1 order was remnants of the whole fish fillet (3 little small fillet fish) instead of one whole piece of fillet fish. Felt very cheated. Side dishes was a little coleslaw and baked beans and some skinny looking fries. Pathetic!

I have been coming here regularly as there‚Äôs no other Japanese options in Ang Mo Kio hub.  The QR code for ordering did not work thus a lady staff came over to assist with the order taking on the ipad. When she ran into some issues entering the orders, the managers (in black uniform) did not step in to assist to take the order.  It wasn‚Äôt a busy time. They left the lady staff struggling. I appreciate the helpfulness of this lady staff (Judy)..  The manager could  have given us another QR code to scan when i first alerted them that there was an error with the QR . None of the managers  stepped in to help understand or resolve the issue. There was also no apologies from any of the managers. Another slip of QR was then quietly placed on the table by another staff after the food arrived. There used to be a manager in specs who usually provide good service but he wasn‚Äôt around that day.  Judy was nice enough to come over to check if we got our food promptly. Kudos to her for her attentiveness. The same can‚Äôt be said of the managers.  I don‚Äôt know the role of the managers in this outlet - clearly they did not demonstrate service orientedness or proactiveness when I visited.

Happened to be in Sembawang running errands. Did an online search where to have lunch and Anson Town Bistro popped up. The place was packed on a weekend afternoon when we swung by. Ordered: Pig skin curry chee cheong fun, curry noodles, chicken chop nasi lemak. Must say they serve decent Malaysian-style food. Do try when you're in the area.
Excellent Zi Char place known for its assam style fish head curry ($30). I had belachan kangkong too and it is very fragrant and well cooked.

If u crave for soft-type prata, this is the place for you! The prata has its own unique sweet taste. But to me personally, I would come back for the teh tarik! It's balance between sweetness, milk, and tea was just right. The prata that I would recommend you to try would defo be the plain prata as you can really taste its raw unique sweetness. Give it a go!
Good food attentive service

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Went with a friend from out of town who wanted to hv some chicken rice in a comfortable ie aircon setting. The chicken was tender and rice was tasty but I'm not sure I'll be back. There's too many chicken rice stalls sans a/c that taste as good.

My to go to prata place when ever I have cravings for nice yummy crispy prata! Have been patronizing this shop for almost 7 years and they have maintained their food standards! Mr Sarsi has always been very polite and friendly towards us but it seems like he‚Äôs not working there anymore ü•≤

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Five stars for the service. I think the food was above average. Plenty of parking at basement, so if you're driving to this restaurant there's parking at the restaurant. I love the panfried oyster cake! crunchy on one side - but need to wait about 25 minutes for this to be serve.
Food soso. Some Staff not friendly.
Food is good and affordable... Open till late

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
This is my first time to try Toa payoh branch. Food are unexpectedly yummy!! Especially pork meat ‰∏âÂ±§ËÇâ was well marinated üëç
You can choose to go Ala-cart or buffet, but I advise can go for ala- cart, unless you are super big eaterüòÖ
They serve ice cream too! You can just take by urself, that was so generous, but for ala cart can just go for one cup and $2 from 2nd cup onwards. Buffet is unlimited!
6 of us was just spent $101.81 in total! So cheap! Definitely will visit again ‚ò∫Ô∏è

Patronize this place often, but the food (nasi goreng) has been getting so salty to a extend I've given up! Told them before when I was eating there .... they change for me slightly better, but take away... I had no choice but to throw the food away... waste of time if I've got to go back just to change food

The newly renovated space looks better, and seems to fill more crowd too with seemingly more chef's counters. Food wise, as expected. However, the unagi don I ordered doesn't seem to have as much ingredients as I expected, and was an off balance to the amount of rice that was given. Not sure about other outlets though.

But I gotta praise the service staff for being attentive! I called once for my green tea to be refilled and it was seen to automatically after, which I really appreciate. Thank you!

Did not enjoy it - upsized portion was still relatively small, taste was just mainly salt and soya sauce from their udon sauce. Comparing it to the ichiban dry udon that I had, ichiban is wayyyy better. Udon was not Q, just flat. Probably some cheap variant.

Also be prepared to wait 20 mins in an afternoon with nobody because the ‚Äúchefs‚Äù (management trainee) have no idea how to make the food. I saw them flipping through a printed piece of paper which showed the steps on how to make the food. Imagine that. Subsequently lots of staff were called to the kitchen to help after customers piled up. Imagine a group of newbies making your food. That‚Äôs how it‚Äôll end up tasting.

Tried the fried Rice before. While it looks nice, it‚Äôs tasteless and flat. Very little meat also. Definitely not worth the price paid.

Manager Kim saw the crowd piling up and customers looking increasingly frustrated, chose to turn her head and walk away. Deliberately avoided eye contact with people.
Excellent service & reasonable prices !

First of all, the staff is very friendly. It was full house when I visit during dinner time as I didn‚Äôt make reservation but the staff still service me well to sit outside and introduce me their menu.
I ordered the premium dinner set for 2pax, food is good and appetizing and I think can serve up to 3 pax for the portion so it is totally worth with $39.90. I take away the papaya salad which doesn‚Äôt show in my picture as we can‚Äôt finish and it taste good too.
Will definitely visit again to try something else in the menu.
Is a nice neighborhood Thai restaurant worth visit!
One of the best Indian food I have had in Singapore.

Had very high hopes for their porridge but we were so wrong. The youtiao were chewy and slightly tougher than it should. The intestines weren't freshly fried which was sad coz we were looking forward to it. The chicken leg in my ginseng was really soft  but bland, thought its supposed to be ginseng based. Not coming back.
Family style cooking. Love their fried egg plants.
must order the mala soup hot and the potatoes. definitely my go-to place in NTU for mala
Tried several lok lok, still prefers this over the others. Great food.

Perfect old school western pork chop, the grilled taste was not overpowering and blend well with mushroom brown sauce. No wonder it‚Äôs always sold out!
Was so good that I‚Äôm commenting in midst of eating üëçüèª
friendly uncle too, can see whole team take pride in serving a good plate of food to you.
Great place to grab for some Nasi Padang
This restaurant was awesome! Fantastic service and the food was exceptional. The duck will leave an impression, in fact everything will.
Currently there is no dining in at NTU McDonald canteen. Due to covid-19
Famous for their prata but prata was served cold hence food was average
My family bought dinner almost every week here. Salty-eggs chicken, fried price, beefsteak, fried chicken swing  are  our favourites food here.
great option for a fast takeaway

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Very decent, humble tasting dim sum. Wide selection and for the price, it is well worth. The chee cheong fun is a must, with its preserved vegetable and lard garnish. Very authentic. The har gao is our least favourite; sufficient prawn meat, but the skin was slightly mushy and more fragile than usual.

One of the best salmon sashimi I've had in Singapore! The slices were thick and fatty, and sushi quality was excellent. The salmon made us happy campers. We both had the sets, I had the saba fish set. It was well cooked and tender, and was de-boned as well so was very easy to eat.

Only thing is I didn't enjoy the soft boiled egg that the set came with as I felt it didn't compliment the dish. I poured half on my rice but preferred it without.

Sets are also very pricey.

The staff and service were great and very attentive, even though we were seated outside, we had no trouble calling the staff who seemed to be able to predict when we would need them.
Their food is now more delicious than the other prata shop down the road. I was also taken by surprise.
Very tasty porridge. Used to go to hans for porridge but now this is the go to place. Best porridge in Novena imho
Food taste but need to wait for dinning

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: First time tried its the last.

The $89 Omakase set is a little bit on the expensive side but it also comes with a bottle of sake. The chef‚Äôs selection is not bad and mostly fresh! Uni is not as sweet as expected but the salmon is fantastic as the cut has a good mix of fats in it making the sashimi melt-in-your-mouth üëçüèø
The oyster and scallops are also plump and sumptuous.

Food is definitely great. The chopped pork was juicy and rich with fat and paired well with its light egg fried rice. Earl grey lemon tea recommended. The steamed dumplings here are well done. Service and speed is up there, considering the volume of customers.
Can be a tad pricey, but the value is still okay. Also, it's open to the noise of the mall.

Cycled here, the chicken looks very huge which could be quite daunting. But it tastes good!
The lime juice is very refreshing as well.

We were very happy with the service and food.All the items we ordered,arrived piping hot and was very delicious.We ordered 3 rice,cauliflower manchurian,salted fish sambal,prawn masala, mutton masala with tea,milo and watermelon juice.The total bill was $53,and I think it is very reasonable as their portions are very decent.Thumbs Up Grace's Potüëçüëçüëç
food are less than pictures show, soups are diluted.

Came for their perennial fav Dong Po Rou (Braised Pork Belly). Still as yummy as I rem. Good sauce with the pork which isn't gamey too. But the sambal kangkong was pretty pedestrain. Spent $24 for 2 pax.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: This was a try and first time we ordered. It's really delicious food.. good quality good taste.. surely recommend!
Best environment to enjoy the meal

I used to come here often when I was living around that area. Years after, I managed to visit once more and I‚Äôm impressed that the quality is still there! The sum lor hor fun is a must for it has impeccable ‚Äòwok hei‚Äô. I also thoroughly enjoy their fish soup bee hoon with milk. Service was also very attentive.

Great place for yummy, value for money food. ÊãâËΩ¶Èù¢(rickshaw noodle) was really yummy at $2. Pork noodle has good portion of pork and liver, wanton noodle was delicious. Also love the bak ku teh here (herbal version), and the chilli ban mian. Would definitely be back to try other dishes.

To be honest
One of the better Prata shops
Crispy hot (Most importantly)
Goes darn well with the fish curry (sour to kickstart your appetite)

Parking ample after 5pm and it‚Äôs free

Really can relax eat and chat with friends

Do come and try

(Non sponsored reviews, feel free to follow and discuss about food and places with me!!!)
We had chicken cutlet and fish&chips, each at $7.50 includes 2 sides and bake beans. Really affordable. There's no need to go to a restaurant unless you're looking for air-con.

Tried their live zoom cooking session last saturday.
Fun and relax session. Easy to follow as well.

Ingredient were delivered to me directly, which was great!

Recipe: Surf & Turf
I like the dosay some western, seafood and teh alia ok not bad

Small and cosy Japanese restaurant. This place serves value for money Japanese food but on a higher level compared to sushi express restaurants. Was surprised by the quality of food they offered here.
Lunch at Silk Road Amara with family, food are fresh and delectable. Special thanks to Rui Qing and Jessie for their attentive and friendly service.

I placed an order on the day itself for a party of 10 guests and was pleasantly surprised that the restaurant agreed. What I appreciated most was that I was advised to place the order in a way that would save me money. The food arrived on time and the portions were substantial. Our guests enjoyed the food very much. Thank you!

Went on a rainy Friday night.

Food wise,

‚ñ∂Ô∏è Hot and sour soup, served warm and wasn't spicy nor sour.
‚ñ∂Ô∏è Xiao Long Bao was also served warm with barely any soup in it. I believe the photo would be about to justified my comment.
‚ñ∂Ô∏è Sliced pork fried noodle was really salty.
‚ñ∂Ô∏è Ice barley was super diluted.

‚úÖÔ∏è Luckily service was oküí™

This restaurant has been around for>10years, churning out tasty Heng Hua dishes. Always crowded during meal timing, so expect a 15 min wait and dishes will not be served all a once, so pace yourself.
Loves the HH Bee Hoon as it reminds me of my childhood where my neighbor is HH, auntie's HH home cook Bee Hoon was fantastic. Medium Size is able to feed family of 3 well.
The HH Lo Mee is tasty, my wife's favorite, nice stock. Nice noodle texture üçú.
Reasonably priced dishes, good menu selections.
Still have room for improvement on the attitude of service staffs.

If you want to enjoy authentic and juicy satay, you NEED to get from Rahim Muslim Food!

Each satay is packed with thick cut of chicken meat, it is VERY WELL SEASONED, extremely JUICY and not to mention TENDER!

The satay sauce is more on the watery consistency, and peanut taste is not as strong as it should be. However, it does goes really well with the satay.

On top of that each chicken satay cost 70cent, and its really worth the bucks for the quality it serves.

Quality ‚úÖ‚úÖ‚úÖ‚úÖ‚úÖ
Price üí∏
Overall ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

Was there on 11/2/22 late evening. Upon payment was told  payment by cash as NETS unacceptable. Ridiculous made me to travel to  nearest ATM to withdraw my cash. Please address this matter to your staff that's customer convenient is priority. Will never ever return to this outlet.
Order home food delivery. The food was awesome and taste like home-cooked food. Packaging was neatly packed and delivered in good condition. Thank you for the good service.

It's a classic mexican fast food place, just that it's quite conveniently located right next to Novena MRT station. We had the burrito bowl, and the nachos fries, both of which were pretty good. It's the kind of food that I'll have for a quick lunch, but I'm not sure if I'll enjoy a proper sit down meal here necessarily.
Delicious food and good service! Thank you!

$122 for 4 pax!

Thumbs up to the staff for their attentive  service üëçüèªüëçüèª

Food had been great!
Love the veggies dishes!
The young adults definitely will love the skewer options!

Worth to return for more
Ordered Cabbage Chicken, Fuyong Omelette, Peppered Salt Fried Cuttlefish and sambal sweet potato leaves. Fuyong Omelette not great, the rest good. Reasonable pricing.
Nice ice cream especially the mango sticky rice ice cream! Recommended to try out here. Hopefully can try out their waffles in the future!

Great for value Thai food!
Nearest MRT is Taiseng, a short 100m walk and you‚Äôll see a stretch of food stalls.
Place is cozy, and has very Thai ambience. Food is 5/5, but space is limited. Service can be better. Overall, food is good! Great cost performance value.

Purposely went there to have takeaway from Boon Keng as they have promotion using Amex. But is a little disappointed compare to the taste near to BK Station, I ordered the usual dishes I always did. The coffee pork ribs and pork belly wasn't really good. The chicken is still good. They didn't give enough ginger and chilli tho.
Fast serviice nice cook.boss and workes very friendly.i like that.üëç

Decent sushi at an affordable price.
If you looking for quality, this is not probably the best place.

Like quite a few and also felt sad on some too. Ikura gunkan is yummy and love the spam. Truffle Chawan and Hotate sushi is okay. Get their salmon, will not go wrong. Sashimi still ok. Oyster look good but doesn't taste nice.

Get their normal Chawan more worth it and delicious.

Every $20 spend can play claw machine catch ice cream.
Professional services. Helpful staffs.
Good when you need a quick bite. Curry O, deep fried Squid and dry Laksa are my regular choices.
Abit different from the usual ramen broth since this is halal. Overall not bad experience but not my cup of tea. Ambience is good. Try out for novelty.
One of the best, if not the best Hakka Restaurant in Singapore. My favorite salt-baked kampung chicken #freerange
Very authentic Thai food. Must order lemon steam seabass. Fresh n soft. Price reasonable.cuttlefish also tasty. üëçüëçüëç

Just want to say thank you and congratulations to the crews! The two days opening specials are crazy especially for them, I got the queue number at 12 and only dine in at 8 yet it was definitely satisfying. The crews did extremely well to cope with the demands and imagine how much pressure they have to handle whole day from the customers. The manager even came to apologise to me for waiting so long which to me is already going extra miles for the customers. Keep it up üí™
Great spot to satisfy your craving for JB lok lok! Authentic and nice! Personal favourites are the oyster mushroom, broccoli and fish fillet!!!

01:07/19
The Argentina beef is tender but not beefy like American Prime Beef. The salmons bake rice with egg goes very well with the cheese. Both dishes are ok but the portion is rather small. Will probably return for 250g waygu beef next time. The service staff is fantastic.

My family always brings guests here because the quality is consistently good. Service also two thumbs up (unless it is crowded, then it takes a while for the food to be prepared and served...so go early!). Comfortable atmosphere too. Even though it is in a heartland mall (Northpoint), the quality is still good.

So far almost all the dishes we've had are delicious. I've probably had 1 or 2 that weren't good but that's normal for every restaurant. The thin bee hoon and lychee pork ribs are staples for us. There is also a green juice that looks like a health drink, but I promise it tastes 10x better.

We brought a couple who just got married there, and the manager carved a pair of swans from a watermelon rind as a surprise. So sweet.

Putien isn't cheap but worth the occassional splurge!

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Went in at around 5pm, there were not many people so maybe there is no time limit for the mookata. I was allowed to eat the buffet until 7+pm with my family. Even though there were only 2 or 3 waiters, we were serviced really promptly and kindly. Overall a pleasant experience. The food is slightly savoury and salty and has a very large variety of meat to choose from ( ranging from pork belly/slices/neck to lamb and fish)

However, the seats and space in the restaurant is slightly too narrow and squeezy, especially during busy hours at around 6pm onwards.

Unique mala experience. Mala collagen soup was unique, tho less spicy that the usual mala stall so do get da la at least if you are a spice lover. Dry mala was good, especially with Maggie noodles inside. Must try the potatos, luncheon meat, lotus root and fish which are deep fried before adding into dry or soup bowl. Eggs are scrambled to perfection and supper yummy!

Alright! It's well deserving of their ratings... Staff are friendly and helpful. I would recommend anyone to come and try their dory fillets and bentos anytime.

The location is in a accessible location with nearby parking. so whether you are coming via public transportation or private vehicles you can always get a slot at your convenience.

Enjoy their hearty meals and story of Tamako!
Standard drop. Eat @ after lunch time 2pm no people but the egg prata didn‚Äôt taste great like last time. Curry is good.
We love everything here from the juicy xiao long bao to the Chinese Pizza with juicy and sweet meat inside crispy dough to the hot and sour noodles which was chunky and the red bean pancake. ‚Ä¶

Tucked away at a corner of Toa Payoh central Larder Cafe offers nice juicy burgers for meat lovers. Good size dining space with approx 12 tables catering to different group sizes. Online Menu, Food Order & payment online, great for tech savvy people, and food was delivered promptly. Overall nice place to have a quick bite and fast service. Thumbs up!
Cons: Wafer ice cream dessert took quite awhile to be serve though. No free water.

Price was OK, portion is just nice. The Penang Char Kuay Teow is average, fragrance is lacking, kuay teow is decent. Prawn is fresh. The chendol is also average, the bowl is small, enough as a dessert for one person. The Klang Bakut Teh is interesting. Price is reasonable and overall taste and quality is above average. Served in a heated claypot, the dish remains warm throughout the dining. Few things that is notable are the rice that is not warm and the tau kee is chewy (fried and soaked). There are a few pieces of different cut of ribs, pork belly as well as some button mushrooms. Broth is mildly spiced and tastes better with garlic. Do get the extra youtiao for added texture.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: The food is AMAZING. Idk what‚Äôs it called, but yknw like zi char sweet & sour pork , they have it here but it taste SO DIFFERENT from the zi char kind. I had the ja jiang mian, the noodle is soooo good. Sorry I don‚Äôt rmb the names of the dishes üôÉ My friend said usually the place is crowded but that day I went was alright. Will definitely come back here!!
The basmati rice is not really up to standard anymore, but overall I feel that it is a good place for the usual fish curry meanl
Fusion Muslim Japanese food must try

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content:
GF-322T dt.15Apr2022. self-pickup.
Delivered wrong items Gobi Pakoda and Veg puff for Gobi65 and Paneer Puff. Last time they skipped one item. Beware of this kind of cheating. I gave a chance but got cheated again. Grab should black-list such cheats.
Last timeMasala Vada tastes so horrible like a rock!

üëç for Friends and Family.
Love the ideas of personal pot as you get to try different flavours when you eat with friends or family.

üíïService‚Äôs quite fast, and the staff are attentive and friendly. Even though the portable gas seems to run out very often, the staff are quick to fix it.

ü•© Ingredients are fresh and very well presented with wide selections!
If your table ran out of space for the food, they will provide food trolley / cart for your food. My Favourite will be the Teochew Style Fish Paste & Beancurd Skin.

üåüComfortable and relaxing environment.
Will definitely return again.

Recommended casual Thai restaurant in Aljunied area! The restaurant is clean and cozy with friendly staff. They also have quite an extensive menu, so it‚Äôs best if you come in a group so you can try more dishes ‚ò∫Ô∏è
