Don‚Äôt forget to get their Red Ruby too!! üíì
Ordered Fish & Chip and Chicken Chop both were great!

Awesome old school Nasi Lemak. Eggs are nicely browned and the rice still smells of coconut, not always the case these days. Sambal was lovely too! Begedil was not to my liking though. Chicken wings were pretty good, with juicy flesh!

Yummy and nice to have in amk coffee shop
Will return and hope standard won‚Äôt drop

I tried sea food horfun. The ingredients like prawn. Fish slices and sotong is fresh and they cooked it well. My Indian neighbours recommended it to me, he used to come three times a week.the atmosphere is casual and relax and enjoy. The assistant is helpful when I asked her for e address, and she said can call them.
Authentic flavors and friendly service all at a great price. I will return to try more dishes.

I was prepared to give one star after reading the reviews but man , the hospitality , food , taste it‚Äôs all top , truly fantastic Resturant and experience not sure why this place got low stars it‚Äôs simply delicious  , hontooooo nii oishi , watashi wa daiski sakana chan
Food is well prepared. It's basically good Zhi char in a simple sit-down setting.
Mee siam was too sugary sweet.
First meal after the SHN. It was delicious. Perfect steam fish. Yum yum

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Good food! Clean environment! Decent pricing. Nasi padang has extortionate prices at some places but that was not the case here.  Had a super satisfying meal. Will definitely return again!!
Very tasty
Deep fry is the only choice. Relatively small selection. Pricing to portion ratio can be high. Coffee shop can get pretty crowded in the evening. Parking may be a challenge.
ordered myself a chicken chop & totally enjoyed #alwaysAfirst saw they offer a wide menu selection, can‚Äôt wait to try the other items another time

Biryani is phenomenal. The rice was flavorful and the chicken was tender. It's a relatively new outlet, do expect some teething issues and be understanding. I enjoyed their outlet at sembawang over the years too.
Had the Hi Tea buffet. Menu variety for buffet was little. In general a nice spread but not as satisfying as it could be (no xiao long baos). Would recommend their ala carte menu instead.

I ordered takeout from there. I actually went to the next shop meanwhile that order preparing and thought grab it after coming back few minutes later. When the ticket number crossed over, the Chinese woman over there yelled at me because she had repeatedly called the number but no one had come up to receive the packet.

If the given time has passed or the customer has still not picked up their food, you should keep that separately so that they can pick it up later.

Even if other customers are watching what is happening, do not shout in a public area.
Used to be awesome before Covid but many great dishes vanished and now it‚Äôs still good food but with a less nice selection and unless you are close by no longer worth the trip

Food was below average. Had the chicken soup which was bland; garlic bread was ok. Steak was tasteless as well; though to be fair the meat was done to medium rare as per my request. Dessert was chocolate cake that wasn‚Äôt great.

I won‚Äôt be back.

The place was full. We made a reservation for 1pm and was seated in around 1.10pm due to full seating.

Food was served up considerably fast after ordering. Taste wise the food was good and the price is justified. For the premium price, the taste was premium too.

We had the noodles and congee as mains and they were just fantastic. The congee was well cooked and the taste blended in perfectly. The noodles were springy and the meat (Irish fat duck) was so juicy. Combined with their delicious greens and signature sauce, it is something you won't taste in hawker establishments.

Dim sum wise we had the harkau and liu Sha bao. Both were well presented but only averagely tasting. Har kau skin was too thick, and lacking in taste, despite the full filling of prawns. Liu Sha bao was cute but also lacking in flow ability and also buns were not fluffy enough.

Overall, it was a very good lunch and we would definitely come back again due to the friendly service.

One thing that can be improved is the speed of serving drinks so that we can remove our masks.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Very good and tasty Indian recipes. should definitely try biryani, tawa fish, chilli chicken and chicken lollipop. Very nominal price and friendly staffs and excellent chef, Will visit frequently.

Delicious food at an affordable price, with a good variety of options. Only issue is finding a seat during peak meal times, and about ten minutes wait for the more popular stalls. Otherwise, it's one of my favourite places to grab a quick meal either alone or in a small group.

Great ambience, nice deco plus 5 stars for presentation! Melted nacho cheese dripped over the entire Wagyu burger served with fries. Lovely idea. Was expected a patty but it was yakiniku Wagyu but I'm not complaining cos it was well done. Impressive. Just didn't like that fries served was only warm, likely fried and put aside for quite a while. Waffle and chicken wasn't that fantastic according to my lunch companion. But still, decent for sure. Wash it all down with a pint for a wonderful dining experience.
I like their fried kway teow. However, my friend didn't think much of her prawn noodles.

Quite a special menu with jumbo frankfurter, bacon carbonara, aglio olio and mix n match options.
Thumbs up for the chef's meticulousness to every last detail... During Sat peak dinner every pork chop that came off the grill was lightly dabbed with a fresh kitchen paper towel to absorb the excess oil before serving
Great relaxing dinner with a refreshing glass of Dunkel from Otto Berlin Haus... One glass wasn't quite enough. Btw this is a drinks stall with quite a history.
Note, try not to sit directly in front of the mala stall. The fumes from the frying nearly killed everyone nearby but thank goodness he keeps his frying short... Gonna try that mala sometime.

We take away our food, we chose the Prem Buta Bara Don but when we opened it when we reached our house they only give the meat but no rice but in our receipt is we paid for the dish fully so it was supposed to be with rice. Very very disappointing.

Surprisingly tender and succulent lamb ribs with smokey vibes. The drinks stall, which I understand is owned by the same owner, carries Archipelago Brewery creations that would complement the smokey bbq meats perfectly. An excellent gem hidden in an industrial estate!
Absolutely best nasi goreng kampung in Singapore
Waited 30min before getting in. This is comfort food for me. I love snowcrab croquettes, and mentai ebi sushi.
Their buffet is definitely more worth it then their set meals üòÅ

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Good that they are quite accommodating with special requests (like how I needed the meat to be portioned)

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
This is the first time I got here. For lunch, it's better you go before the lunch time, example 11 a.m. So you don't have to que.

I ordered:
1. BBQ Pork Dumpling Set
2. Roasted Pork Vegetable Set

For restaurant, the price is affordable. And for the meal, it's delicious.
Good food and excellent service
Ramen is good, soup broth is very nice! Price is on higher end, but overall great!
Long queue. I dont like the sweet corn side dishes.
Yummy satay!!!
Good place for weekday lunch. Generous servings worth your money.
mutton satay is the best there!!!

One of the popular malay stalls with snaking queues on weekends which is a testament to how tasty the food is.
A stall serving malay style dishes which are nasi lemak,mee rebus,mee siam, lontong, mee soto which i believe are their best sellers. From my observation from patronizing the stall, most people will buy their nasi lemak as their sambal is delicious.
Although my favourite food and recommendation will be their mee goreng and mee rebus which will not disappoint.
Service is fast and efficient despite the snaking Q ,so be prepared to Q for a good 15-20 minutes.
Food is affordable between $3 to 4 per meal without additionals such as fishcake,chicken wing etc..

Best ‚Äúyusheng lohei‚Äù I have ever tasted. 5 kinds of fish, octopus, ikura; with all organic vegetables & fruits complimented with special plum sauce that‚Äôs not too sweet & really refreshing on the palette. This dish alone is worth 5 stars ‚≠êÔ∏è!
Signature fish soup with rice crackers was spot on too. A must try here.
Special chicken, Wagyu beef, Boston lobster noodle, dessert were all very good. Such an enjoyable dinner.
Very satisfying meal for both me and my wife - the taste exceeds our expectations and the portion is generous. Will certainly return for more, especially to try the other items on the menu. üòã

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Good food. I enjoy the service even more. Go on less crowded days  like weekday morning to enjoy a relaxing vibes.
Food is nice and unique ! Xinghua beehoon, the signature dish is super fine and tasty! The sweet and sour pork meat is really tender and the soup has a very sweet after taste. All marvellous!

Great hygiene, always good roast duck, never disappoint.
Slightly understaffed but every crew member was doing their best.
First charge to debone the duck.
Charge for extra herbal sauce on the duck, which could be complementary on request.
Great handmade jade tofu!
Enjoy this delicious nasi meal from Assam tree, hidden in NTUC Ang Mo Kio (outside the Amk hub mall)

I had my dinner (4 of us) @ Northpoint, had the doutou/clams, 100seconds croaker fish (we got 2 üòã), loufa, all dishes were yummy.  Service staff were friendly and cheery.  Happy and delicious dinner !

This stall is newly opened. I only managed to try the Homemade Coleslaw and Cheese Tofu Fritters. I quite like the coleslaw.

=======

I came back two days after last visit, and ordered:
- sirloin steak
- salmon hollandaise
- sotongyaki

I changed the sides to coleslaw and potato salad. Coleslaw's standard is as good as last visit, and potato salad is nice too. For the steak, quite good for hawker standard.
Opens late and now with new app ordering service

We tried out their promo menu as suggested by their staffs‚Ä¶not bad at all..

Their pastas are nice‚Ä¶ too bad.. forgot to take the picture of it.

Came on the recommendation of friends. The place is actually made up of a Teochew restaurant, a dim sum stall, and a drink stall. Private rooms and airconditioned sections are available. The charcoal fish-head steamboat came out with a battered pot and sooted chimney, signs of frequent usage (popular dish). The soup was creamy and salty which suits my palate (unlike other brands that tend to be slightly sweet), and the base used in the soup was fried fish. I could taste yam, prominent salted plum, and butter. Belachan chilli was not spicy despite the mean look. The other unusual stuff that came with it was the shredded fried egg. The raw fish slices provided were fresh. We also tried charsiew bao and liu sha bao and were not impressed.

Cosy place with good food and great service. A wide variety of dishes are available and on weekdays, there are lunch sets. The food portion is generous and balance of taste is just right. Prawn paste chicken is a must try. Will definitely return to try more on the menu.

The fried fish was too dry.
Kuey Teow and others were okay
But the service was terrible, especially the one cashier lady
Average Indian food. Was told chef different so tissue prata was different from usual as well?
1/6 ordering kisoks down during lunch period. No one manning the physical cashier.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Still the best chicken rice in Singapore! They do also have a decent zi chat menu that offers the usual dishes you would expect with the sweat and sour pork chops and sotong you tiao that you might want to try. Good service and it‚Äôs usually quite busy in weekends.
Always come for chicken chop with spaghetti. Bangs for the bucks
A bit difficult to find seat during peak. The claypot rice is not bad. Chicken rice is fragrant, oily & nice. Chendol is quite miserable without much ingredients. Overall still ok.
Nice scenery....good and friendly service....food is very good....
Budget steak for quick bite.

Great food at a reasonable price, everything is grilled on demand so the food will be hot and enjoyable. I ordered the chicken thigh don.

I do not like the kimchi that is served with the don as it's supposed to be Japanese food - not a fan of something sour, even if its purpose is to be an appetiser.

Would not recommend the sliced beef don as it is too salty.

food is great at good portions and reasonable prices. there's a wide selection of western dishes so it's worth a second visit to try more.

staff is friendly and helpful. there's a fired oven for your pizza so you have a real authentic taste!

Wow came here and eat at 4pm still they serve the food item hot and yummy.

Chicken wings is must :)

Absolute garbage. Tried it before 2 years ago and it was pretty good. This time I thought to order the bowl. Paid 18 dollars for it because I decided to add extra unagi and beef (sold as roasted striploin). Food is just microwaved meat on iceberg lettuce. (Picture is as delivered)
Cheap food, affordable meal
Old school authentic Japanese cuisine that has been around for a long long time...
Xing Hua is very family friendly and has a sumptuous variety of food. Highly recommended :)
Awesome enviroment and best diningüëçüëå
Very very Nice so delicious

Overall it was a happy & very pleasant experience dining here!

Good job on the attentive & personable service by the team.

Enjoyed mooping, pork belly, mixed vegetables, pineapple rice, olive rice and mango sticky rice. My family members love the spicy lala, tom yum soup etc. I don‚Äôt take any spice so will have to take their words for it.

Ordered many dishes, too hungry to capture all snaps:)
Hotpot is great!! Must order beef.... absolutely üíØ% recommended ‚ù§Ô∏è

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: for hawker/coffeeshop is ok. value not that bad. but I feel seating slightly cramped as the tables and benches are fixed.

I ordered dory,and they had problems finding it,I guess... It's been 15 minutes and counting... I see some people have waited 20 minutes...
I think they really need to review practices or they'll be out of business soon

Heard many reviews about this nasi Padang stall in blk 128 Toa Payoah lor 1, happened to be nearby and decided to give it a try. There wasnt any queue when i was there. There were only 2 pax infront of me. Selection of dishes was quite limited actually but went ahead to order.

Ordered the rendang, stir fried spinach and a slices of omelette. Bill came up to SGD$7.50. Have to say that it was quite expensive.

Food wise, rendang wasnt too bad. Have to say, portion of the rendang was quite alot. The spinach and omelette was normal. But have to say their lemak chili padi gravy was very different from others.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
(Translated by Google) The taste can also be cheap

(Original)
Âë≥ÈÅìËøòÂèØ‰ª•‰ª∑Ê†º‰æøÂÆú

It was my first time visiting this place for dinner with a friend on a saturday evening .
The restaurant was small with limited seatings.
Not so organised maybe due to the small area.
But the ambience was cozy.
We ordered 1 satti sooru each and hardly couldnt finish due to the potion.. hahaha.
But well the food and drinks were nice though .üòä
Price was ok also.

Table wasn't properly cleaned when we sat down.
Had to request for staff to help us clean it.
When our meals came, we also had to specially request for staff to put the sour cream topping on the baked potato. But I guess they were short-staffed.
Quality of food; seems to have dropped over the years. But I like the fact that the ribeye was a rather good cut, not too fatty/chewy. Though the blood and sauce and oil mixed together wasn't a very pleasant sight.
Too expensive, would only come occasionally.
Food is not cooked. Waited for 2-3hours for the food to come and the food is so cold and disgusting. Food and drinks are all overpriced as well. Please don‚Äôt come as it will ruin your day/ night.

I like the Truffle Mushroom Melt and the salad is very fresh. I recommend the sweet potatoe fries. Many place couldn't achieve the crispy or it will become soggy very fast. But here the fries is nicely done, no fancy seasonibg just true skill & true taste of the sweet potato.

Osmanthus latte is too sweet for me. Has ordered for less sweet but myself still find it sweet. Seem to me like Osmanthus honey in latte. Personal opinion.
really authentic Thai food. The basil meat rice is very nice

Likely what sets this place apart is the service. First time at putien and noticed the great service. We received a free chilli bottle per person as they‚Äôre celebrating their 20th anniversary. Food was slightly pricey but the quality was definitely higher quality yet with better higher quality ingredients. Worth to try the Yam, Sweet and sour pork.
A bit overpriced for the food... Fast and efficient for some Mexican themed food.

Great concept! Affordable cook your own lunch with team mates / dinner with friends session in a condusive small group environment. Our session was a paella night, $60 per group of 5. As shown, paella kit was provided. Totatally enjoyable...we went hungry, waiting and salivating. When its done, we just ate right from the pan at the induction stove. Every group will somehow find their own cosy corner. Small pot of paella yet satisfying return for everyone.  Friendly instructor and crew who will drop by to guide you when you need a tip or 2 during the cooking process.

Booking was promptly responded and payment was easily done through bank transfer.

Thumbs up and definitely recommended! =)

[Added - Mee Hoon Kueh lunchtime session. Awesome fun during lunchtime...though it states 45minutes in total, prepare for 1.5hr to cook and enjoy your masterpiece and hangout for awhile at OUE social kitchen.
Very JENG yixia worr... I very likey the signature pork rib soup. $12.90 for standard product which come with 12 ingredients... Very FRESH too the seafood üêüüêüüêüü¶êü¶êü¶ê
Foods were so so only. Staffs were super not friendly and were super attitude.. Unable to arrange for 7 peoples but able to arrange for 6 peoples. JOKE OF THE YEAR 2022. Á•ù‰Ω†‰ª¨Êó©Êó•ÂÄíÈñâÂêß
Don‚Äôt let the name and decor out you off. The chefs know their stuff here and the food is actually really good and the pricing is also good. Service is disinterested but good enough. Enjoy!

Was looking for coffee after dinner and stumbled upon this cafe. Big and spacious dinning area. There is also a huge alfresco dinning area where you can bring your pets along. Very comfortable environment. At around 9+pm was still quite crowded on a Friday nite.

Cafe pricing is on the pricier side for this order. Drinks are quite unique. Ordered the iced puffed rice cafe latte and a hot speculoos cafe latte.

Puffed rice went quite well with the latte adding some texture. Giving a cereal feel when it is soaked up with latte. Recommended to try. Speculoos latte is ok but hope that they can be more generous with the speculoos topping.
Cheesecake is average.

Nice place to chill after dinner. Will be back to try their food.
Good food and service. Too full!!! We enjoyed the food alot and will be back again.

The steak was delicious and not too expensive. The atmosphere of the restaurant was really nice as well and the service was top tier, they were very polite and friendly. I saw that some reviews had mention a long wait but I did not experience any problems in regards to the waiting time. Definitely worth a try and would go back there again.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
the worst mkt in sg. (only this outlet)
stuff was throwing ice at each other and making the floor wet while customers were just bedside eating. took forever just to get our order. VERY BAD HYGIENE.

Had mutton briyani and teh Tarik.
The mutton was so tender, curry fragrant.
Best mutton briyani I had.
The place has is clean. Staff are friendly.

This western stall has a Âè§Êó©Âë≥to their food. It‚Äôs like old style western food they served back in the days. The chicken chop and gravy was quite tasty. Coleslaw was quite nice too‚Ä¶it had pineapple gave quite a good flavor I think. The queue is very long for weekend dinner times though. I waited for over 30min. Not sure if it is really worth queuing up for, but worth a try if the crowd is not too bad.
Food delicious and price reasonable.new location now accessable by mrt.coffee shop also has lots of fans very airy.

This was where we held our wedding. I liked the flexibility of being able to upgrade dishes from the cheapest plan to those that we liked better. I also appreciated other perks that were included in the package including the printing of wedding cards, wedding favours and free corkage.

Owen was an amazing coordinator who never failed to respond to my questions and arrange to things I require on the wedding day. Wendy helped me on the actual wedding day, leading us in and out of the ballroom for changing, as well as with the tea ceremony.

We were also able to book a meeting room at the Grassroots' Club separately for our tea ceremony which made things really convenient.

My guests loved the ballroom and food and we had an amazing time all in all.

Thank you so much for helping us hold such a successful wedding! Eternal Garden Restaurant has proved that you don't need to hold your wedding at a fancy and expensive hotel to have a wonderful wedding. Would totally recommend this place if you're looking for a small venue for 50 to 100 pax though they can probably accommodate up to 200 people too.
The steak was great. Soup was so so. Dessert was one scoop of ice cream. $7 add on for soup and dessert not very worth it. Service was not bad. Not crowded, so quite comfortable.
like the fried  pork belly in fermented sauce and garlic prawns and signature thick black KL noodles amd steam chicken
Dinner serving is awesome. Great ambience for a meet up.
Would do well to learn their p's and q's.
Dropped my egg on the tray. Didn‚Äôt apologise and PUT IT BACK INTO MY BOWL OF RICE.

Delicious food at reasonable price and  in cosy cafe.  Loved the curry noodles here, tasted like the ones i had in JB. The chee cheong fun is worth mentioning as well, silking warm rice rolls with i think is fried onions which is very flavorful. The nasi lemak is not as good but worth a try. Ample parking lots situated right infront of the cafe. Will be back to try more of other chee cheong fun flavors and definitely the curry noodles again.
Such a good place to eat the meal.

Came here for lunch, on a Sat afternoon. Very friendly staff. Loved the ambivence, mordern Thai themed decor with contemporary thai songs in the background made our lunch very enjoyable. We will be back!

Splendid, 24 Hours, customers queuing and best of it is I work here ! Just joking

( Hi owner, my just joking means That the outlet is popular because of Me working there, sorry for the confusion )

Anyway one if your staffs, which I can said is my colleague, Named David is a very cool and nice guy. No bossing around, no putting on airs, very patient with me and understanding too. He's a great guy.

We Tagaki Ramen at AMK is Hydeine 1st.

Perhaps our taste palette have changed.. these American style barbeques just don't satisfy anymore.

The lamb shoulder for example, I'll have the Chinese style ones from ÂàòÂ§ßÂ¶à anytime.

As for the beef brisket, I can't quite say it was Ê≤πËÄå‰∏çËÖª, for it left behind such a greasy sensation. Even for the taste - we asked for salt and pepper half way through the meal.

So, I think we'll have our BBQ meat fixes with the Chinese joints.

Called in to reserve and true enough the place was packed up very soon. The pull pork burger is tasty and flavorful. The duck confit is made just nice. Loved it. Draft beer was having a promo - buy 2 get 1 free. Overall great service, ambience and best, no service charges.

I was having dinner with friends at Happy Joy,and the food there was tremendous and we really had a sumptous meal.The Service was great and the waitress were helpful.Thanks for great meal there and keep up the good Service.Will catch up again soon.
Good food. Great service. Reasonably priced.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Love the food there. Will always come whenever im nearby.

great surprise to find a legit sichuan food restaurant in this area! The ÈÖ∏ËèúÈ±º is extremely affordable and good ($14), highly recommend! The cucumber side dish was a bit too vinegary for my taste though
Decent mee soto and mee rebus but I prefer their satay.

Nice place. Tried Fried chicken chop Nasi Lemak $5. Taste so so. Rice not so fragrance. Tried Dry Mee $4. Taste also so so. Curry chicken cheong fun $4.50 is good, curry is great! This I will recommend to try. Coffee also not bad.

Always enjoyed the food. Haven't been to this outlet for years and noticed there's new items on menu. Tried fried vegetarian dumplings and its awesome - with crispy thin skin and spicy pickled vegetable tats not too salty.
Had this seafood pot recently and its taste was really refreshing. Slightly sour and spicy at the same time. The ingredients were fresh and certainly goes with a bowl of white rice!
Good food, good service. Value for money for chinese buffet.
My go to place for nasi sambal goreng. And my alltime classic kuihs..
Taste, hygiene and quality has improved significantly. Hope to dine-in more frequently here

The portion size of the ebi salmon ikura don is paltry.  The staff also served us the wrong food items - ebi salmon don without ikura and salmon mentaiko don - and I had to highlight this to the staff. The wagyu stamina don I ordered on a previous occasion was also mediocre and had too much vegetables. What a pity‚Ä¶

Its more for kids. The lay out, menu choice, automatic food delivery trains, plush soft toy collectibles etc...The portions are small. Tiny bowls of rice/noodles. Typical adult will need 2 portions (cost about the same as any typical Japanese restaurant in Singapore). They also give out tokens for the claw machine located outside the restaurant. But its almost impossible to win/grab the ice cream out of the claw machine.

Ramen - ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ
Soup - ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ
Meat - ‚òÜ‚òÜ
Gyoza - ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ

Slightly on the pricier side but as authentic as it gets.

We ordered Set C (s$46) which consist of a Jjajangmyeon (noodle with black bean sauce), a Jjampong (spicy seafood noodle soup) and a Tang Su Yuk (sweet and sour pork). On top of that we separately ordered another Jjajangmyeon (s$10.80) and a fried chicken with garlic sauce (s$32). This is good enough for 4pax. The noodles were well prepped and flavorful. The fried chicken was really spicy but shiok! Also, they only serve free flow preserved pickles, kimchi and raw onion as side dishes.

This restaurant has no reservation system in place so do visit early to avoid queuing!

I have been eating here for long time ( may be frm  May 2019 )
as I like Indian food.
Since Feb 2021, they have all new staffs are working there and I am realizing, their food quality has decreased now.
It not taste good as before.

Don`t see Ravi also sitting there.

One Suggestion for this Indian restaurant:  Please manage the food quality and the taste you had like before..
Definitely a must try place! Affordable nasi Padang, mee rebus, mee siam & many more. Food was so good which you won‚Äôt be disappointed üòç

It a nice and good place to enjoy indian food
With family and friends
Overall, they still retain the old school western taste...it‚Äôs a must to drink their Kopi if you are a Kopi lover! üòâ
Food was amazing! Awesome briyani! Naveed delivered customer service very well. Will definitely come again!

The sushi off the conveyer belt tastes a bit stale but the menu items are pretty good. It‚Äôs a little pricy and I expected more from the food.

Service staff was friendly but a little slow to respond due to the small amount of floor staff working with a huge holiday crowd.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Tender chicken spicy sauce. Food is fresh and tasty. Portion is reasonable. However during peak hours expect a Q just to order, then another 10mins for the food to be ready.
Should those food over nice to try
Old school western food. Friendly auntie
Good service, affordable pricing, generous portions, tasty food.

I rarely will leave bad review on food cos to me, as long as u have food, u shd be blessed
BUT NOT THIS TIME
ordered stingray fr 2 pax $15
I am always super fine wf not cheap food as long as it does justice
Stingray is super small like 2 small slices and super duper dry n hard to chew :-(
Cockles costing me $9 for 15pcs is half cooked n cant swallow too cos despite chewing few times it is still a whole chunk
Paid $26 for 2 rice, 15pcs cockles & 2 small slices ray, it is a disappointment experience

Eat at yr own high hopes !
Food is good and tasty. claypot seafood noodle is so so.
Good place to have nice crispy Prata with Fish or chicken curry. It's hard to stop eating at one prata.
Used to quite like the food at GYG but the standard at this outlet has just fell off the cliff. Had the burrito bowl which had a pathetically small portion. Food was rather cold. Disappointing.
One of the best hotpot places in the northeast part of sg :-) you can share the soups too. The service varies depending on the server but 80% it's good!

Restaurant level food at neighborhood prices. Be prepared to wait, or share tables with other customers. Patronized 4 evenings ago.

The yam was a pleasant surprise. Plain looks, but fried with a little sweet taste. Great with beer. The chilli was the best accompaniment with the other food.

The lor mee is white in color. The taste reminded me of fish soup w milk. The fried mee sua is also packed with flavors.

All in all, a hearty meal.
Nice and affordable
Limited promotion but still the staff is very friendly

The juiciest pork tomahawk I have ever tasted.
So good until I have to get a takeaway shortly after I tried it at the coffeeshop itself
staff generally pleasant. Prata, nan are good whole the bryani serving is generous. overall quite a good meal experience there over the few times, I hv been there.
Staff was very friendly and pasta was warm when served! New in campus!
This Boon Tong Kee outlet is probably the nicest one I‚Äôve been too so far! Very upmarket feel with very reasonable pricing. The service was also great!
One of the better Thai food so far. Reasonable price for a Coffeeshop.
Reasonable price

Had dinner at the United Square outlet. Great food and even better service. All the staff that served us were polite and helpful - if only all restaurants and service staff were like this. My wife requested for a knife to cut the saut√©ed broccoli we ordered as she found the pieces too big to chew. Even though they didn't have a knife, the manager kindly offered to bring our broccoli back to the kitchen and to have them all cut into smaller pieces. And all done with a smile. It was a very pleasant dinner and we'll definitely be eating here again soon.
one of the best mala fragrant hotpot i ever tried. good balance of the fragrance and taste.
Had food poisoning after having the the lobster and chicken combo, with the lobster soup. You might want to look into that.
Went for lunch, Nasi Padang is nice especially the curry gravy. Dont forget to buy Kueh Lopez is super soft and melts in your mouth.

As others have said, the quality of the food did not match up to the high
price (about $9). The pasta was inconsistently cooked. If you have a pasta craving within this area, I think Pasta Express or Tea Party are better choices.

EDIT: It seems that there are many 5-star reviews posted recently‚Äîmake of that what you will.

I arrvied at about 11:45am, no queue. $3.50 set comes with 1 egg, 1 chicken wing, peanut & ikan bilis. Added Otah $1.

Rice has mild pandan & coconut fragrance, not over whelming but just nice.

Chilli goes well with rice, not as spicy though to me.

Chicken wings is crispy and well seasoned.

Normally Singapore Zin char food flavor is quite good but very heavyÔºåjia kut. However this restaurant is not. The flavor is mild and not strong. It‚Äôs perfectly seasoning. Seems no burden to your body. The knuckle is good and no porky. The fried bee hoon is so delicious and have so many textures, crunchy, fresh , nutty and savory. Must come and try. Total bill SGD14.5.
Food is really good. The truffle beef was delicious, the beef was full or flavour and tender.  I dont usually like salad but the ones they served were so fresh i ate them all too.

10/10. Staffs friendly and accommodating. Will come back for the angry bird again.

30 June 2022 : back here again after 2 years with my family + master chef and sad to hear no more angry bird. but food is still awesome. Lady boss still very friendly and shop hygiene upgraded alot. Cheese tofu is now my new favorite thank you. Highly recommended.
Wide variety of food! Comes with drinks too.. love their satay!! The BBQ meat portion comes in pretty big portion so careful when ordering..
Crowded during the weekend. Not enough staff. Food quality is ok. White Pepper Crab is nice.
The food was pleasing to the palate and we appreciated the warm and meticulous service. Our server was Andrew; props to him.

This is still the Japanese restaurant I goto for good variety and good valued set meals. The negative point is that you have to wait a long while to be seated, probably becoz the food is great and value for money. Though I felt the staff should be more organised and alert, not to let some patrons laze in their seats for long time even after they have finished their food. The pork miso soup set has lots of vegetables, nice amount of pork and the soup base is tasty. The beef in the cheesy beef set, is tender and well seasoned; with the cheese elevating the tastiness.

When visiting I usually stay at Sofitel City. Used to eat at Xi Yan in HK for imaginative and delicious modern Chinese food. The new Xi Yan Maxwell with a great bar is also truly amazing. Next to Tanjong Pagar MRT
Noodle Al dente and dumpling solid packed with filling

Limited seats ramen served warm not hot at all Self pick up and even condiments just grab as u wish as the condiments fill up to only 1/4 of it waste of container. And no Hygiene put in place when they won't notice if I throw back any unused condiments after I took them out for says 45min. But staff was good tho will give it a 3 for that. Not recommended for anyone who loves their ramen to be served Hot.
I tried the herbal fried rice and recommended kouro pau, I love it and also dapao for my family. Will revisit the shop when I am nearby Novena.

Went for Sunday dinner. Definitely not busy which is good. However, for some reasons the staffs are difficult to find. There were only several tables occupied, the fact that the staff are not around is a bit frustrating. Food was not at best, not bad either.

Pretty decent tongkotsu and miso ramen! The free ramen noodles top up comes in a huge portion. Knocked one star off cos personally I found the soup on the saltier side. Otherwise glad to have found a 24H ramen place!
Ramen stall inside of coffee shop that offered tonkotsu, spicy and miso based ramen. The ramen is good and most importantly affordable. For a good bowl of ramen with less than S$10.

Good place to get consistent good quality xiao long bao  the rest of the dishes were quite yummy too lole the wanton in spicy sour sauce, the garlic paste pork and the zhajiangmian. Service was efficient and polite. Lunch for 4 pax came up to be $105. Will continue to patronise the restaurant just for the xiao long bao.

Honestly a hidden gem! Food items on the menu are pretty pricey but they always have promotion on Special dishes like Peking Duck, chilli crabs which make the visit a fairly sweet deal. I love the KL-styled char siew and Peking duck. Definitely worth a try!

First time trying. Food is really yummy, friendly staff. Menu is large.

Looking forward to my next visit.
Been lunching / dining here for the past 10 years, very yummy food especially the chicken and never disappoints! This is definitely one of the best Chinese restaurant around!
Just a normal Fish and Chips, nothing astounding. Fries quantity was pathetic, should have provided more.

Food taste is good but portion and price have seem to reduce and increase respectively. We ordered via FoodPanda a half of the Duck Roasted with Angelica Herb at $34 which honestly isn‚Äôt enough for 2-3 adults compared to 2 - 3 years back when we had them in the restaurants.

mutton briyani - very hearty and tasty, thick gravy, flavorful rice and tender mutton; a cut above the rest that you would get at typical Indian Muslim restaurants. I‚Äôm a fan of thosai too and theirs doesn‚Äôt disappoint, it tends to sell out by around 11:30am on weekends. Volcano prata is yummy too with runny yolk, crispy prata. Comfortable and clean air conditioned environment

Food not as good as what it used to be.

Soto is diluted and the soup is cloudy unlike authentic clear soup.

Mee rebus is super thick and just does not taste like the authentic Malay mee rebus.

Mutton Satay is tender and peanut gravy is good. At last.. we can enjoy the satay.

The use of paper bowl and diaposable fork and spoon is a good improvement to avoid cross contamination of food.
The takoyaki is delicious üëçwith squid filling
having a set dinner for two costs $48++. It is worth it. I love all dishes. It's nice and more than enough for two people. It is highly recommended.

Visit this shop early in the morning to meet up with friends. The place is not crowded. Alot of seats are available during my visit. The service is as expected in an Indian Muslim restaurant. They will accede to your request without hassle. The food we order in the morning are the obvious, which is Prata. The crowds start to build up after 8am. If meeting friends or just to fill up for breakfast, nothing fancy, this place will do.
Good prata
No frills Zi char stall...but quality not as good as before..just stick with the usual noodles and rice dishes, avoid pairing dishes with steam rice...

Excellent foods and delicious.
Probably to take away as the network's signal is very low in that lot.

Had the clay pot rice. Serving is disappointingly small & is nothing like the picture,  Dried pork sausage & salted fish was not added, let alone the spring onion.
Taste is OK tough

The claypot rice is very nice! Small portion just for 1 pax, we ordered the medium portion for 2 pax which is $15.80. San Lou beehoon‰∏âÊ•ºÁ±≥Á≤â is nice too, while the crispy tofuËá™Âà∂ËÑÜÁöÆË±ÜËÖê is tasteless, it taste like the fried frozen seafood tofu.

Given a restaurant without aircon, the price is on high side, total bill $52 for 2 adults and 2 kids.
Food seems overpriced with poor presentation... Service was okay but the plates, especially the one for the soya sauce, was dirty with stains.

Great variety of main courses, side dishes, and lots of dessert to choose from.

The creamy chicken pasta was great value. Definitely wished that the pork-steak portion was bigger because it was very yummy. Sandwich and truffle fries was ok. Spinach soup was so so, served hot so that‚Äôs good.

Waffles is crispy on outside, light and fluffy on inside. Please safe some space for the waffles :)

Great  1st time there. Food quality is good, plenty of sitting, orders can be made via QR code of ordering machine located in store. However price a little high. Almost comparison with the Japanese restaurants. Thought it should be slightly cheaper considering it being food court concept. Nevertheless, it was a pleasant lunch.
Good for breakfast

I'm not sure about the high rating for this place, perhaps I didn't order the correct dishes or the dishes are not to my liking. The dishes I had were just okie - sweet and sour pork, Assam fish, french beans, fried chicken Italian style ?! (The sauce was strange ), corn soup, tofu and fruit platter. I prolly won't come here again.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Best prata banjir I ever had

Wanted to give it more stars. But as the dishes come, it got even more disappointing.
1. Tang Hoon is completely tasteless. Please skip it.
2. Red Ruby desserts came with ice cubes and not iced shavings.
3. Worst Thai milk tea drink I ever had. It is completely diluted.
See photos.

Great Food. Friendly Staff
Will return to try more

It would be really crowded at night and in the evening but you should be pretty fine if you are visiting in the morning or in the afternoon. However, the dining area is a bit small and cramped. A significant portion of the tables and chairs are placed near the toilet and washing area, so hygiene concerns may arise, especially at this point in time. The strategic position near the entrance of Boon Lay MRT Station while being situated in Jurong Point is very convenient. The food is generally good, though there isn‚Äôt a wide selection for vegetarians. I hope this commentary would be of use to you. Have a great day! üòÄ

minis promo for burrito seems smaller than usual ü§î
limited seats for dining in
staff didn't know table numbers during serving
but at least there's table service üòÜ
Yummy chicken  chop

Horrible service. I understand that the server doesn‚Äôt understand English. At least staff should have basic training to learn stall‚Äôs dish names. Nvm, so happen that a lady before me orders fish and chips, so I told the staff ‚Äúsame dish‚Äù in Chinese. After 15 mins of good wait, I was being served a chicken cutlet instead of fish. And the staff still insisted it is fish, despite it‚Äôs definitely chicken just by one look.

The lor mee is alright. Found much seafood and aromatics in the soup. Like dried shrimps, fried shallots and sliced red onion. However the ceiling needs mending. Found a cockroach leg on the table and I blew it away. Fortunately, it did not end up in my bowl of noodles :/
As always, great chicken rice. Good service.

Bought 2 egg prata, 1 plain and 1 cheese prata, when i saw the pratas i was shocked. It was small and not fluffy at all. And the curry taste weird. My husband and i wasnt even full after eating the pratas. And they charged me $7.80 for the pratas which is not worth at all. I will not buy from here again.

Visited twice when the restaurant newly opened to try out their promo dish. The Hana Bara and the mentaiko salmon don. Both dishes, despite being lunch promos had generous portion of ingredients. The third time, I ordered mini hana bara as takeaway and was so surprised to see the generosity in one bowl (assorted sashimi, unagi, aburi salmon and more)! The sashimi was very fresh and had crispy crunchy bits to give the dish a perfect finish. I hope this place stays open so I can keep coming back for more Chirashi!
Five stars . Good place for respite when overwhelmed with the university work. Loved the lunch menu variety. Steak was great and sides were a great complement.
Briyani was fragrant with lots of spices and herbs. Mutton curry was also good. Worth trying.

Price is a little on the high side but it is reasonable for the superb quality of the food. Wide array of choices from Yakitori to ala-carte dishes as well as a few choices of Don. üòÅ sashimi is quite fresh too!

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Tangsuyuk, sweet and sour pork is the best. Come many times to try this dish.
Had the three-kinds butadon and all three kinds of pork were amazing! Different textures and flavours and all of them were great!
Had veg briyani here. Food is tasty but portions served are ridiculously small for the prices they are charging.
good food and affordable, will definitely come back again!
Delicious! Rendang quality flux slightly, meat at times rather tough.
Stall selling various soto, gado2 and satay. Most of the time long Q
So so food n price high

Its terrible here, the cleaners clear the trays and utensils and literally SLAMs them into a dirty box. Its so noisy you cant eat in peace. Imagine whacking a dirty bowl really hard into a big black box filled with dirty bowls. Horrible place my first and last time here

Service was bad. Food was worse. Had pork broth and tomato corn soup base and they were not good. I thought the Paradise brand prides itself for being a top player in the market. Well, this truly was disappointing. Water had sand grains at the bottom of the glass, and when asked about it, the wait staff couldn't explain and hey, no apology was given. I couldn't even make out what they served for dessert. Not coming back to this outlet for sure.

Avoid this place ! Just had bee Hoon goreng topped with a Sunnyside up . Came without the egg and only maximum 5 small cabbage . Asked for the Egg, that guy just took from the leftover tray probably in the afternoon. And best of it with a the tarik , the damage was $6.30 ... Inflation ?

I love Guzman Gomez's burrito bowl! Filling and tasty. Will try to request for more onionsüòç in future as we used to be able to scoop the amount we want, but due to Covid they now prepack them (garnishes and sauces) in separate small containers. Love my burrito bowl with plenty of üå∞

On 28/5/22,i bought my parents to try genki at jurong point for the first time,i had good experience from other outlets and thought i would have the same here too but to my disappointment, it was a let down on the services,lady at the table infront of us was getting up to get her food (okonomiyaki stick) from the train which was situated at the third level, when she was taking it off,the train begins to go back, she did not manage to catch the plate and the food flew off to our table and landed onto my mum's dress.The mayo and sauce smeared all over my mum dress and they did came immediately to ask what happen ,then proceeds to just clean up.While it is not anyones fault,we thought that we could have at least gotten a sorry that this happen as my mum was visibly upset.

Even though they were swift to clean up,it was not cleaned,the bonito flakes were still on the sofa and some sauce residue, thus we left that seat empty and switch sides.The manager just explain that the kitchen will allow the train to go back when the food is unattended for a period of time.Overall not a very pleasant experience,we quickly ate and left,hope that it shall never happen to anyone as there wont be any sort of compensation or even a single apology,have to deal with it urself okay.

It was made in favour of chinese tastebuds, chilli wasn't sambal tumes (malay pronunciation) sambal was light brown, when u grind more onions but use little chilli,  only about 4 dishes to choose from, fish cake, hotdog, chicken wing and ikan bilis with peanuts. Small cup of green nasi lemak rice. Price though was the deciding factor for the 26 odd people in queue on a wednesday afternoon at 12pm. 40 minutes in queue. Will i crave for it again? No. Was there anything else in the coffeeshop for alternative eating? No.

Poor customer service, the elderly women serving the food has a frustrated look on her face all times, super unwelcoming, when asked questions, she just turned her head and walked away, not replying to my question

Super long waiting hour, took 30 minutes for a table and then 1h30mins more for them to finally serve all the food, the Shengjian Bao and Tangyuan took the longest and wasnt even that nice. I am very disappointed upon the fact that they have a 4 star review but it was one of the worst restaurant i have ever been to

Bad food quality, the Shengjian Bao we waited for the longest was as hard as a rock half of it was soft half of it was hard, there is also not ginger to pair it with the Shengjian Bao and XiaoLong Bao. The vinegar was also diluted.

The price is also expensive for such little food with no quality

I can understand why we needed to take 30 mins just for a table, because they took so long at serving the food, the items on the menu is also so less yet we waited so long just for a simple dish

Pretty decorations in the restaurant.

Foodwise the dishes are pretty awesome. Tried the 4 pax set c and the portions are super abundant.

Highly recommend Daphne's service!

Black Bean Sauce Beef Hor Fun $8.
Hor fun so smooth and soft. Beef is tender. Sauce is tasty.  V wok hey type!  Absolutely tasty!

I tried their Sum Lor Hor Fun ($8) before. Also v v good!  Hor fun is always so smooth and soft. V tasty and wok hey taste dish!

So far, I always walked out of this restaurant totally satisfied!

Highly recommended!
Worthy
Food is pretty average but price abit ex for such standards. Fries abit tough, chicken chop abit dry. Hope they improve as they are newly open.
Come and try.. üëç

One of our favourite venues for meals when the family decides to eat out.
The prices are reasonable and the portions are rather huge so it is value for money.
Being a member gives you 10% discount.
The lava cake is superb.
Not wanting to be bias, should visit this restaurant at least once and decide for yourself. At least satisfy your curiosity.
Only inconvenience is that no booking or reservation is allowed and you have to queue up like the others, but if you have time to spare, give it a shot.
Very good service and wide range of food selection.
Snack

Good ambience, great service and awesome food
Ordered the aus waygu beef medium rare! It was perfectly medium rare! Savoury, well seared and melt in the mouth :)

Impressed with the otoro roll, iberico pork jowl, egg plant, black truffle udon and matcha pannacota!
Food is ok but expensive
hidden in a humble kopitiam in ang mo kio. nice variety of dishes. tasty curly fries with just right crispiness. buttery corn. mushroom soup was nice too
Express kiosk for takeaway only besides taxi stand...prices abit high like those in yum cha rst to me... Haven't patronize for a long time
I luv the Pao fan and vege..

I packed dinner back. The dishes are simply delicious.

The Mixed fish Tom yum soup was nice, fish hor fun was tasty, and the fried rice with pock chop was simply good enough to fill m6 teenage son's food cravings.
fancy and clean place in ntu, nice to have an important appointment. however, the service is not good with the slow waiters and waitresses, which delays everything
Love the Prata and teh tarik! I usually take out. If you don't mind dirty chairs and small spaces, you will have no problem dining in.
Good crispy pratas as usual. New set up.
Go for the salmon bento. Best value for money and taste.

Love the taste of the food. Taste healthy and delicious. I would definitely return to try the other food on the menu.
Hopefully they don‚Äôt increase the price further.
I would not recommend getting the membership if you do not come often as it is not very worth it.
Hair in the rice rollüò¢
Great food, one of the best spring chicken that I've tried, may have to wait a bit (10 - 15 minutes)
Love the promotional items. Value for money

Great place to chill out with friends. Their seafood is pretty decent and fresh. I like the razor clam dish, they cooked just right and it's fresh too. This dish price is pretty cheap compare other seafood restaurant. Price is reasonable and service is okay.

Lack of hygiene in this place. The new plates that were placed on the table were so still so oily. Shows that they were washed properly. Secondly, most plates were dented and not presentable at all. Service was very slow. Prata was really good. 2 tried two types of briyani. Both were equally terrible. Prawn of not fresh a all.
Ventilation of very bad in that shop. The place were they dumped all the leftover food was so unsightly and unhygienic just the sink were we wash hands. Walking pass there made us want to throw up. Please review the hygiene practices in your shop . Thank you

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Latest venue .... not fully renovated as air con wasn't up though.. food wise.. is solid... In charge was kind enuff to explain that air con will be up in a weeks time due to renovation and apologised for any short comings during payment...
Nice food and servive here! great place to chill

Located at Royal Square ground floor. From outside may not be obvious and gives more of a bar & wine establishment vibe which they do offer, but I'm addition also serve Filipino dishes. They also have options for typical western food like pasta, etc. Milkfish is not common a dish in SG so this would be a good intro to Filipino food.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Cosy little place serving nice korean food ! Very big portions and we can‚Äôt really finish our food. The staff were really friendly and would offer to split food into our bowls. Prices are on the higher side so while I would come back, I wouldn‚Äôt come back often. Music are a bit loud at times so could be hard to converse at times.
Personal favorite cold crab (not cheap), braised duck and cai Poh Kueh teow and orrh nee. The rest of the dishes are okie.

It's OK but really nowhere close to nice or a place I'll visit again.

Place - this place is very small with around 4 tables, each table can sit 2-3 comfortably or squeeze 4 to 5 pax but not recommended. Looks relatively dated, nothing to look forward with nice or decent ambiance for the likes of mini restaurant.

Food - nothing to look forward, noodles are just cooked with some sauce, nothing flavourful. Xiao long bao is worse than those you ordered at kopitiam.

Price - fairly affordable considering its a mini restaurant below public housing HDB, nowhere close to any amenities. Do note they accept Cash only, no cards or QR payments.

Overall I'll give a modestly 3 stars it's OK. But it's a place I'll never want to visit again.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
The food is excellent, generous portions and prices are reasonable.

They do catering as well.

The drawback is the lady boss is not patient.

The salmon slice is very thin and doesn‚Äôt look fresh. The salmon belly is worse. So tiny, Feedback to the staff and say it‚Äôs normal size 5 tiny slices for $11. When I say Tiny it‚Äôs really tiny. (Size of abt 2cm x 2cm and 5mm thick?) my customer whom I brought him there is in disbelief of them serving us such standards.

I buy anywhere for $11, it‚Äôs definitely going to be bigger.
I won‚Äôt go back anymore.

I have attached the photo they show they will serve. Actual per slice is maybe 10% of what you see. They told me picture for illustration only. I was‚Ä¶. I didn‚Äôt managed to take a photo as my client finished it himself as it‚Äôs too little to share. Order at your own risk.

The unagi set w egg was still acceptable as in 5.5/10. Not fantastic but ok.

Ordered the medium serving claypot rice, added a lot of soy sauce myself and made sure to mixed like siao. The claypot rice was slightly bitter giving a lot of charred flavour to the dish. It tasted quite good! Chinese sausage egg omelette was delicious, bitter gourd soup was simple and nice. There were no customers when I ate there today hence my orders came within 10 minutes plus.
Their food is great! The restaurant is clean and the staff are very accommodating/service oriented.
The closed at random times and don‚Äôt update Google. Don‚Äôt bother coming as they are likely closed. Told me there is a ‚Äúsign on the door‚Äù that they are closed so I should have know!

Best hidden japanese food in Tai Seng area . Open till late , friendly staffs , great service , good food and what else to ask for ! Highly recommended place . Great skilled  chef working on immaculate food .
The go to halal seafood to go that is nearest to Sengkang.
Good not bad , services is good, clean nice new environment
Good food and price affordable.

I came here during lunch time... I tell you guys, the queue is darn long... There are only 2 workers working, 1 at counter, 1 inside the kitchen.. orders are moving at snail pace... 40 minutes to get to my order... They could only pack 1 order every 4 minutes... So please order online prior to coming down to save time.
Great food at good deals! Worth having the Samosa with the Mint Chutney! Pair it with Badam Milk, Rose Milk or a hot cuppa tea for the perfect tea time snack!

Super delicious noodles! Authentic taste with lots of options... My friends had the signature rice noodles and I had the pudding rice noodles - both were extremely good...will definitely be back soon :)
Service was also very warm and friendly.

Go for their Steamed Fish with Lime. Really pack a punch! We also had the omelette with rice which was yum too. Easy and affordable menu, but delivers in terms of taste, service and quality. Plenty of seating space and a drink store where you can order something to put out the Thai spicy sour fire üî• Highly recommended.
Great thai food and excellent service. I'll be back often enough I'm sure.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Great place of a good and affordable meal.
We went lunch on Sunday. Order tom yam soup and few dishes. Realize the soup was served with few pieces of mushroom and 2 pcs of slice squid.. Very pathetic seafood soup. This is my 3rd visit h

This place serves nice Hakka dishes. Very homely & comfy vibe inside the restaurant too. Went there during off peak timing, so it‚Äôs not crowded at all. I ordered rice to go with the dishes, but next time I‚Äôll order porridge rice insteadüòôüëç

Not recommended. Tried their parents' day set menu. Food was soso and portion was small. Overpriced ($230 for attached w 4 teas). Service was not very good considering that it's a restaurant. Elemen is so much better.
Nice view n great food...

My friend went to the restaurant earlier to have seat inside while waiting for my lunch time.

The staff just told him straight in face that if all the customer wait like you, die lo! Wish a very harsh tone and loud that every diners around could hear. And keep on staring at him as if he got no money to eat and wasting their space for siting there and wait for me to come to order.

If were you, what do you think?

When I'm in the restaurant,  while eating. A group of office personal having their lunch and their last course is Yam paste. They requested for 2 small bowls bt in the end they didn't use it. The staff while clearing the table after they left, say very loudly that "WA GET 2 BOWLS FROM ME AND NEVER USE"!!!

I have gone to this stall since I was young. In my latest visit today, I realised that the uncle has increased the price from $5.5 to $7.5 (L). I thought knowing the uncle for so long, I made a friendly remark that he has increased the price again. To my horror, he started scolding (very fiercely) at me, angrily returned my money and brushed me off telling me not to come back anymore in future. I knew all along this uncle has been rather rude to his customers but little did I expect that on myself. It says a lot about a person to drive a customer off in this manner, let alone a loyal customer for so long. Honestly, there are many other very good penang prawn mee around. He has lost me and my family forever.

Fantastic place with good food!
Had the garlic naan and naan with butter chicken. They have a wide variety of food and beverages, Briyani was a very big portion, so if you are really hungry, go for it!
Can‚Äôt wait to come back!
Food taste good. But place abit cramp and price abit on the higher side.

Very good food and service. The abalone, LALA, and Yam paste is a must try!!!

Our waitress Wendy Tan really went out of the way to make us welcome.

üòçüòçüòçüòç WILL COME BACK AGAIN!
The food here doesn‚Äôt fail to satisfy at all, with a large number of hidden gems on the menu. Superb food from this outlet too ‚Äî as always!

Hidden in a HDB estate in Ang Mo Kio inside @johnsoneatery332amk
which serves up bowls of ramen at very afforable prices. Arguably one of if not the cheapest ramen you can find anywhere in Singapore as their cheapest bowl of ramen here goes for only $5.90 that come with an entire torched chicken drumstick!! I was in total disbelief. The torched chicken drumstick is also available as add on to other ramen at just $4. Also their broth are made in-house and is boil for 15-hours.

What I tried,

Shinjitsu Ramen‚Äôs Tonkotsu Special (S$10.90)
Come with four big pieces of sliced chashu, a giant sheet of nori, and one ajitama egg, which had been cut in half. The tonkotsu broth is smooth, rich, flavourful and not too salty. The ramen noodles soak up well of the glorious richness broth. The chashu has a delectable smokey flavour, my only gripe is that it's slightly dry but that‚Äôs just a personal preference.

Shinjitsu Ramen‚Äôs Red Spicy Tonkotsu (S$8.90)
Pack with a pile of spicy minced pork and three big pieces of sliced chashu. The little bits of minced meat added a nice contrast to the smooth noodles and rich broth.

(Add on) Torched chicken drumstick (S$4.00)
I choose to add this to my Shinjitsu Ramen‚Äôs Tonkotsu Special ramen. This large drumstick has a gorgeous sear on the outside and is fork tender soft succulent. Absolutely delicious.

Pork Gyoza ($6.00).
The gyozas here are handmade fresh. Generously stuffed with minced meat and spring onions, and each bite was springy and juicy with the skin being thin, slightly chewy and a lovely charred bottom. This is a champion.

Grilled Squid ($6.50).
Big chunk of squid. Soft and tender not jaw inducing chewy, and you can just bite through. Is amazing.

Very affordable yet quality not compromise. Is really value for money, delicious for the price paid and generous in portion!
used to be good when it started out. karaage is crispy and the cutlet is piping hot. but my last order were neither of it. suspect they prefry and left it there sitting
Not eating there often now after they change their side dish salad. Last time was fresh salad, now is those similar to KFC type. Yucks, I hope they change back.
Love this place for lok lok. Great soup bases. Value for money given 3 different ways of cooking

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Very authentic HuNan food!

Very nice ambience and friendly waiters.

Dinning areas are decorated with a mixture of Oriental & Western feel, very comfortable.

Best food will be the Roast Duck, very succulent. Following fried prawn üç§ with Bonito Aioli. Crabmeat Ee-fu Noodle üçú is nice.
Overall not bad. Fries so so.

Food options can look quite overwhelming because there are so many options available from Indian to fusion to western.

Latest dish tried was their chef's recommendation - maggie goreng. Can't really imagine paying $4 for maggie with no meat (but got egg) - but it was so good! Maggie has a nice smokey wok-hei that I was pleasantly surprised by. It's not oily too.

However, maybe not get the thosai here. Not sure if the standard has changed but I tried that twice and both times the thosai took a long time, felt like it was made from ready made flour and came with watery curry. Prata was meh.

I'd recommend the goreng dishes instead :)

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: A wide variety of dishes. We ordered garlic pork, honey chicken, deep fried sweet and sour fish, fried enoki, deep fried squid, green curry, phad Thai, broccoli. Portion is huge, price is reasonable, food is delicious. Phad Thai and green curry are my favs. Its not crowded as well. A rare gem indeed! Will definitely be back for more‚Ä¶ Boss is friendly and service is great too!

Poor Service

The staff was unfriendly and difficult to attend to my needs when only my group of friends were the only customer there at that time.

Simple-looked japanese restaurant & offers a variety of high quality donburi (rice bowls) at affordable prices in a comfortable and affable ambience. Their flamed seared grilled meats was a great highlight n premium quality used but we take a step back n try their other dishes. Wow... Equally good n oishi. The garlic edamame once eaten, I can say u practically can just go along with their liquor n chit chat with friends. It's not too garlicky n u won't have the "green" taste of peas. Next up is the chicken nanban don, avocado salad n saba shioyaki, brings out the perfection in each dish, balancing each component‚Äôs texture and coordinating their flavors so that all come together to create the awesome taste, tantalizing your taste buds....

The tangsuyuk was very good. Shaped more like a fry than a cutlet it was crunchy. Had an argument with my hankok gu because she ordered the original soju flavour when I wanted the blueberry flavoured one. She called me a noob. Tmd. Dulan. Team blueberry pls like my review.

Order some dishes like vegetable, fish skin, fried rice and noodle. Fish skin is serve promptly but the vegetables are serve after 25min of waiting had to complain to the manager to get them to prepare the rest of the food which took more than 40min to serve fried rice .. the noodle is not even prepared yet.. had to ask them for plain rice for my son first while waiting.. guess we aren't paying enough for the restaurant to notice our order..

The mala fish soup was really flavorful, with a bit of chinese wine. Beancurd skin is a side order. The spices in the meat skewers were good, masking the gamey mutton taste. Spicy chicken is unique, not your typical flavor. But a bit on the sweet side.
didnt take much photos. but it was really value for the quality of meat.

Ordered chicken katsu but they gave me some frozen chicken drumlets instead. Curry was some powder mixture as well.

A home kitchen at best.
I love their winter melon vegetable. But its not always available. My mom and i would eat here after most of her polyclinic visits.
Poor service.. long wait for collection when tour group came in tho I already made payment. Then forgot to put in one of my dish.. check before you leave.

Always a great food experience here. Coin prata nice and crispy. Mutton bryani was tender and flavourful. The sweet lassi was good as well.

This prata shop is definitely much better than the one at Jalan Kayu. Might be abit out of the way but worth it! Prices about $10 per pax with drinks depending on what you eat.
Beef hot fun with egg sauce was so delicious! Value for money as there is set meal for 6.90  for the big portion of seafood Mee hoon soup and a drink

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Nice food nice service
The service was efficient. I had the chicken cutlet, everything was fine except for the hard garlic bread.

I truly enjoyed the lunch here with family members whom we have not dine together for 2 years! Ordered the set for 10 paxs and portions were huge but satisfying.  The collagen barramundi dish is amazingly delicious.  We were very satisfied. Only drinks could be a little on the high side.

Very very good prata and teh tarik place. Came here because girlfriend doing manicure nearby. I thought it will only take 15minutes but Im wrong. In the end, I came inside this shop twice and to chill twice. Love this place!

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Portions are hearty, kimchi and other small side dishes can be refilled. Not quite used to Korean style of Chinese dishes, taste OK But no wow factors.

The last time I was here must have been over 20 years ago‚Ä¶ same familiar taste, very authentic Hakka. Just like how my grandparents used to cook. Must try: salt chicken, bitter gourd Yong tao fu with the bean broth‚Ä¶ and abacus, of course.!  Even a simple noodle with minced pork.. al dente! Or QQ :).  Way ahead of Koo Kee‚Ä¶ Place is simple even though aged.. personable service, like you walked into someone‚Äôs home. The patriarch pacing around the restaurant‚Ä¶ and complimentary sweet potato  black sugar ginger syrup. restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Had been here a few times before deciding to drop a review for them.
The place is clean and well ventilated !

Most of the time we are here on weekend afternoon, slightly less crowded compare to night timing. There's aircon, so no issue even if you crave for mooks during lunch ~ Be sure to drink more water mannnnnn~

Staffs are friendly, but tends to get a little busy. So do give them more time for the preparation of your orders, or additional orders.

There's two type of choice for this mooks i believe. Buffet Style or Ala-Carte.

Most of the time, we will opt for Ala-Carte. Each plate range starting from $2.00 , if i didnt remember wrongly. On the pricey side, but for the location & air-con , acceptable la.

Love their minced pork & bacon cheese ~ The rest are good too, but personally skip black pepper, too heavy for me. But teriyaki pork belly is great !

There's also FOC ice cream for you, just help yourself to it.
Great fix for midnight cravings, open till 2am .

One pointers for all customers, do take note yourself on what you have ordered and no. of orders. Although as the usual practice, at most mooks, they will combine your no. of quantity into the same plate/bowl, sometimes there's still a few missed/overlooked orders. So if in any doubts do ask them, they are nice people so dont worry. At times, it happens to be a missed for our favourite meat, so we tend to realise.. Hahah, else i think its easy to overlook for everyone, too much selections too much orders. Just whack all the meat ! Hahah.
Excellent ramen‚Ä¶ just like Tokyo.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Tried a plate of their ‰∏âÊçûÊ≤≥Á≤â. Plenty of fish slices, hor fun had nice wor hei and flavor was just right. Probably one of the best I had tried. Will return to try other dishes.
Tried this restaurant using Burpple Beyond. Got the beef Don which was surprisingly good. However it wasn't the cheapest, would definitely recommend to give it a try if you have Burpple Beyond.
Meat is slightly dryer but the soup & ramen is good. Love the gy≈çza.
Food is alright. Service is slow. I mean if I am supposed to take my own utensils stop putting them inside the counter.
Claypot chicken is really good!

I had ordered a Mee Goreng last, last night. We waited and waited. We saw them serving other customers first. (we were regular customers in the day, so they probably did not recognize us) After 45 min, a customer said that is too long and left. So, we decided to go also. But before we told them we are gonna leave, we asked them if they are going to give us the food. All of the workers in the restaurant were very responsible except one person. He is the person at ordering station. After we had asked him, he said that if you can't wait, then leave. We had waited for almost 1 hour.
The cook came and said that he already cooked a lot. That is when the reason for the problem came. The person who shouted at me actually served his regular customers. The cook knew us. He tried to calm me down and gave the food to us. We said thank you to the chef and left. So, only the person who was at the the ordering station was irresponsible. Now, you might know the reason why they serve your food very late. Thank you for taking your time to read this!

Fav mushroom cheese prata there‚Ä¶ now you have to place order at the cashier. Service is bad nowadays.

Hygiene wise is bad. Oily utensils.

Last visit I order green tea‚Ä¶ and in the cup of ice, there are seeds- looks like lemon seeds.

Asked the staff he say he don‚Äôt know‚Ä¶ never even offer to change!

Nice crispy prata - we ordered plain and egg prata. Definitely one of the better pratas I‚Äôve eaten. Outlet has both indoor and outdoor seating. Didn‚Äôt ask us about our preference for curry though - we were served fish curry. Curry was ok, a tad watery for my liking. Overall, good deal via Shopee voucher.

Had the pork and chicken katsu curry. For the quality of ingredients,  taste, price and availability, I would give it a 4.5 star. I will definitely visit again. Btw, Katsu is amazing especially for this price point.
Delicious food at reasonable price üëçüëç repeat visit.
Today I visit one chuan restaurant the food is testy and service very good

What we ordered:
Onion Cheese Prata
Plaster
Egg prata
Coin prata
Dessert Prata (Red bean)
Bandung

What we will come back for:
Onion Cheese Prata
Egg prata
Try a few more of their unique flavours

Pro tip:
Go on fave and buy their e-voucher. You pay $27 for $30 credits. Save $3! üòÅ

Their shop is relatively small even with outside seats I would say the place can only take a max of perhaps 40-50 people with safe distancing etc.

Thankfully we arrived before the dinner crowd and managed to snag seats in the air conditioned area. We got the side seats by the wall and the seats are essentially just concrete. Quite uncomfortable honestly.

The drinks came rather quickly and then soon most of the other pratas started being served up. They also provide curry as seen in the picture for free. If you want sugar with your prata you can also ask them to pass a bottle to you. In essence service here is pretty good even though they are extremely busy.

The onion cheese prata and the egg prata was excellent. Super crispy and tasty as well. Would highly recommend!

The plaster was quite meh to me and the dessert prata is similar to the chinese red bean pancake you have in restaurants except its much sweeter and also the red bean is not as fine and fragrant. I would give this a miss the next time.

Bandung is ok. Big cup is sizeable but because we make our own bandung at home we prefer it more gao with more carnation milk and syrup. This was a tad bit diluted for me.

By the time we completed our entire meal plus drinks our coin prata had not been served. Not only ours but the tables close to us as well. We thought good things are worth the wait... right? Wrong! We totally disliked the coin prata and ended up not finishing it. It was so thick and so much flour even though it was crispy it was just too floury for our liking.

Will we come back? Definitely! This place is right beside Springleaf MRT along TEL MRT line. See how I rated them on the individual components.

Location: 5 üåü
Food: 4 üåü
Ambience/comfort: 3 üåü
Cleanliness: 3.5 üåü
