Food wise, value for money. But one thing I never like about this stall is, the queueing system. No one bothers to organise the queue. Sometimes when you stand there, you don't know if the person in front has ordered or not. And the owner and assistant don't care. When you try to order through the assistant, he will tell you chef will take order from you and hack care. I never like this type of disorganised queue system. If not for my kids, I won't bother patronising.

Ordered masala thosai and one of its gravy was totally bland zero taste. After making payment told the guy at counter about it and his answer was that‚Äôs how it is supposed to taste like. Wow. Ego too big i guess. Anyway other food I order wasn‚Äôt nice too actually. Nasi goreng kerabu taste more like rice with white pepper. Good luck to those trying üòé
Great food, great service and great vibes always, a go-to for me and many others here at NTU, definitely recommend it!
Great food let down by below par or disinterested service. Wrong order fulfillment is common.  Ordered egg prata n got cheese prata instead.
Nice food at reasonable price. We came around 11.45am. Total bill was $57.40 for 4 pax. üòÅüëçüèª
Food was really delicious, lady boss recommended the steamed sea bass as it was fresh. Absolutely wowed by the veggi dumplings. Will come back again.

Ordered at 1740. Got food at 1820. Just 2 packet. In fact, the lady that came at 1800 got hers before me. Attempted to check the status a few times and got brushed off, the male staff even told me to not ask him and go ask the one that took my order.
fking best japanese on the go food
Good quality food at reasonable price. Good to dine in with well decorated environment that does not look like coffeeshop. Had pork curry rice and white bee hoon. Was good.

I am a resident nearby and have been a regular at this eatery. We have been noticing poor attitude from the staff. If not for the 4 stars food, yes if you don't mind getting disrespect from the staff, demeaning looks from them, do patronise. They will make you feel like we are the reason for their sad life there. We owe them a living. It is times like this which makes me wish there is self ordering kiosk.

Affordable and good Thai food served here. The price stated on the menu is the final price. Staff there are average. If u want to get the coconut drink, bear in mind that a majority of them are young coconut, hence the flesh doesn't come off so easily.

Some recommendations:
- Lemon fish (Currently having promo at $12.9 per fish nett)
- Tom yum soup
- Omelette

Enjoy! :)

Please avoid this vendor.

This eatery should be boycotted. Ripping off your money for unhygienic food. My Husband waited 45 mins for his takeaway order of 2 mee goreng and 1 nasi goreng thai. Extremely exhausted and hungry on a Saturday night, plus it was raining. We just wanted to taobao food home in peace.

The cook is from India, no offence meant, I am a local Indian. But majority cooks from India working in eateries here clearly do not know or do not bother to learn the local singaporean/malaysian mamak flavours.

Semi-cooked mee soaking in oil and the mee goreng sambal. No eggs, no veg. And the cook had the audacity to stuff the dirty paper receipt (which fell on the ground) into my mee. Contamination. Similarly, prepared oil and rice mix. Prawns were raw and not cleaned for the nasi goreng thai. I was grossed out.

Worst is the packer spills in lots of tomato ketchup, with no cucumbers into the oily mee. Why? I have no idea. Wonder how many people suffered from stomach upset.

Unbelievable mess. I saw many other customers having to remind them their orders.
We were charged $17 for this nonsense. We couldn't eat. Had to throw all away. Such a rip off.

I called up this shop the same night. The person in charge who claims his name is Raja was passive aggressive on the phone, aggravating me further, did not apologize, did not offer a refund. Typical, unscrupulous attitude. He doesn't even feel accountable for cheating a customer. Lack of conscience and ethics. Indecent.

I'm not sure how this outlet is still operating. Clearly the D'Rubinah management does not care despite the numerous complaints and poor reviews against them. They are simply getting rich by cheating customers. Customers (including me but no more!) are enabling these unscrupulous vendors.

Authorities NEA or SFA should look into this place. There's absolutely no hygiene, no actual cooking except slathering lots of oil into uncooked noodles, stuffing receipts directly into the mee. Lack of ethics too. I'm sad the hard earned money went to waste, we slept hungry that night, and even disappointed that the local mamak food culture is rampantly ruined. Real sorry state.

I'm actually furious that my 17 bucks was wasted at this place. No more patronizing at all the D rubinah outlets. Have shared my experience with friends and they too are boycotting this place.

I was here last Sunday evening with my hubby and a friend. The food was really good. We enjoyed it very much. The set meals are value for money and reasonably priced.Ordering is done through our own phone by scanning a QR code.

We were given a seat in the middle of the restaurant but due to safe distancing, we has to sit all in a row rather than facing each other. Would have preferred to sit facing one another so that it is easier to chat. Fortunately I was able to switch my seat after the next table left.

Date of review: 26 Sep 2021
A random find stumbled upon it by chance on CNY, the Maggie goreng was surprisingly good not soggy and flavourful, the teh tarek hit the throat smoothly...
As good as their main stall in Adam Road. No queue.

Very expensive.  Sour pumpkin in green curry but not replaced. Small portion. Paid more than $50 and still hungry. Won't go again. Bad customer service. First time and disappointed. Did not order any meat.

Best curry chicken in Singapore.

The menu is so extensive that we had troubles choosing what we wanted! We settled for the classic curry chicken which doesn't disappoint. The portions are very generous. It goes very well with plain white rice, bread and even roti prata.

Overall a very satisfying meal and would come back over and over again.

Expensive sun in sg
Food quality need to improve to reach sun level

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
We had a delectable meal in this Teochew restaurant. The service was excellent too, attentive and prompt despite it being so crowded. The cold crab was my favorite. I love the freshness, plus the meat was thick and firm. Yummy indeed.

A delightful place to spend your Friday evening.

Reasonably good Thai zhichar!

Their olive fried rice and pineapple fried rice are fragrant and tasty

I happened to walk into this coffeeshop and noticed this stall in the extreme left corner.

From their menu, I decided to have lontong as it has been a long while since I last ate.

I was expecting the usual bland lontong, but was pleasantly surprised by their lontong.

The rice cake was nice and firm enough without it being too soft and lumpy.  The piece of tofu was fried nicely, soft inside but firm on the outside.

The lontong gravy was also very flavorful, and when mixed with their sambal, it turned out to be a very good combination.

Overall this would be amongst the top 3 lontongs that I have eaten in SG.

Definitely worth trying their other dishes the next time I am in this coffee shop.
Price a bit too high! Service good!

Super awesome dine in experience from the moment I step in until I leave the place.

Food plating is instagramable. Food is delicious and very tasty.

A cosy place for catch up with love ones.

Ate there for the first time today. Good food. Wide variety to choose from. Great service.

Decors above the counter remind me of my childhood. The two milo tins and the two pressure lamps.

Will go again to try other dishes.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: First hotpot experience and it was great! The soups were flavourful and the service was good. Location isn‚Äôt the most convenient but I would still recommend!
nice place if want to eat hong kong dim sum, there's vip room if more people are dining, the restaurant staff are friendly too.

My daughter vomited and suffered all night after eating the burrito bowl delivered in the evening. I couldn't complain because I was in a hurry to go to the hospital, but it is a very angry experience. I enjoyed it as a delivery food for a long time, but recently, the taste differs every time I order, so I tried not to eat it, but it became the last burrito bowl. Pay attention to the quality of your food.

very nice food & value for price BUT BE AWARE they are close on every 2ND WEEK of MONDAY (The owner of the restaurant advised that i could update the post...)

All dinners do go on the days; when they have chickpeas & Indian salad that go so well with mutton/chicken/fish rice set

my papa simply love the food there!  me too...  yummy!

Ambience was beautiful, but service time was extremely slow. Cooked food served should be warm but some were not. Our food was uncooked and the restaurant waived off the price for that dish. Not a very good experience as one would have greater expectations given the price point.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: So so, some dishes pretty good some not so. The Mango London Duck taste weird wz the artificial mango essence sauce and the Braised Pork Belly got the pork smell. The Icy Sweet n Sour pork was good, but the ice melted when it was serve causing the meat to be sitting on a puddle of water. Black pepper beef was good too.

Friendly and attentive staff. Nice cosy environment. Food is good and delicious. We especially love the assam curry fish head, quite spicy yet taste good. Do try their dessert as well. Overall worth coming again for dinner.
Nice food, good environment
Waiting time was long, but deserve it. Drunken chicken, curry beef soup and spicy pork noddles were decent and delicious.
Affordable, filling salad bowls. Egg costs an additional $1.20 but it's really good!
Had a good experience here, food was served quickly and was made well. Staff are very welcoming and friendly! (:

We booked for our Primary school gathering ,we have dinner at Semma  Indian restaurant, The restaurant itself is bright and clean, simple layout. Their food was delicious though the spicy level was high .. the staff are very polite except  for one lady she came over and ask us how's the food so we told her food was very nice but the spicy level are high in some food and her reply was   "O uncle every one comes here and say they love the spicy level." but not everyone love spicy right? When we order the food , you were there helping us to do the ordering, you should advise the spicy level so we can tell you to reduce the level for us, Anyways thanks for the help , after that a guy with long hair came and ask us how's the food ,we told him the same issue but he was more polite and friendly to advise us with a better reason.  Prices are easy-on-the-wallet too. thanks to Semma keep it up!
Some staffs are very rude at this branch
Nice nasi lemak, rice is good, wings not bad, side dishes are also decent but chili not spicy enough else can be a 5 star. Overall nice makan!

Tried this place out of curiosity, food was expensive, not particularly great. Order was forgotten and had to ask for it. Flies were present in an AC environment - hardly a great sign of food hygiene. Would avoid.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content:
Third class place. Few days back I went here, and order Chicken 65. However it turned out to be rotten meat ( Kind of marinated for 5-6 days).
So I complained, on google.

Then the chef Velu contacted me and offered refund and requested to withdraw the review. I said ok.

Adter 2/3 days I went there again, he told me he can not serve me as his management has decided not to provide services as I complained 3/4 times.

So they are not interested in correcting the problem , but just want to bar people who complaint.

Done ever go here. All rotten food. I am now proceeding to complain to Food authority. Once the do inspection it will be clear.

If you need Indian food, there are other options on same building and fortunately they don't serve rotten food.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
It was a great place indeed. I honestly went to the market however most of the outlets are closed. Really love to cook fish today.lol.I just enjoy strolling with the windy and warm weather,bought a watermelon juice and just seat here for a while.

Look at the view,it‚Äôs a breath of fresh air,really relaxing.

Let‚Äôs stroll again next time pips.

Went to check it out today.
Me and pals order ramen, and donburi. For the portion of food in bowl, is best value for money. At least for my curry ramen its as close to Japan Co-co ichibanya mild. (maybe can consider to offer spicy level customer can choose?)

The maki rolls are big. The takoyaki squid in it is a lil small, but for the sauce and furikake its as what you get in Japan.

They have a tons of bowl selection of ramen udon and donburi. I might missed it, but somehow i didnt see Tempuradon.

Next time i'll check out the udons and the fry Ebi.

Maybe they should consider serving ocha and chawanmushi too

/come here with base line of Japan street/mini restaurant food. Dont compare them to hotel cuisines
Nice prata but price is slightly on the higher side

Tried during lunch hour. Pad Thai served hot and tasty. Fresh prawns. $6 for a big plate of Pad Thai and $1.80 for hot thai milk tea.  Prices are Nett. They are generous with the portion. Looking forward to bring family along to patronise again.
Food is pretty nice!! Strongly recommend their dimsum and prawn fried rice. The environment is atas and classy !
Varieties of food available, well served by their staff, operating 24hrs and convenient cark parking nearby.

Very popular stall. Broth is pretty decent but slightly salty. I like the texture of the noodles but the slice of pork is not the soft type hence a bit dry to me. I like the gyoza but my partner wasn't impressed.

Was having reunion dinner
Tables were spaciously spaced apart and comfortable seating,
Baby friendly seat and utensils provided
Food was fresh but portions were small.
Dishes were served at long intervals
Was amazed at how my tea was not refilled a single time during the 2 hours seating
Great bowl of ramen for the price! However the pork can be a tad bit dry, however the rest of the bowl was pretty much on point!

My friend took me here as I had just returned to Singapore for holiday- we each had the Kaisen Chirashi ($25.80+), the torched kingfish with crab roe and the soft shell crab. Price is not cheap for the chirashi, but boy, the portions were huge! Did I mention that the variety of fresh fish on the rice was really generous and beautifully presented too? In the end I couldn‚Äôt even finish my own chirashi bowl and felt bad wasting so much food! The torched kingfish appetiser was incredibly tasty and the soft shell crab was nice too. Will definitely be back to try the fois gras and the truffle dishes as that was something I saw on the menu. Place is a bit out of the way though, and seating capacity a bit small.
Staff attitude very bad. Slice fish noodle soup more noodle then soup. Request for more soup even thought we are willing to pay staff gives lots of excuses and attitude. Last time patronising.

I ordered the traditional soup of the day, on a Friday which was stated to be Lotus root soup. However when it arrived they gave us a different soup without informing us. When I questioned the manager about it she told me that they do not need to inform customers about changes of the soup of the day and that nothing would be done to rectify the situation and that i would still have to pay. On top of that she was rude about the situation and she asked me multiple times if i ‚Äòunderstood‚Äô the situation and what was going on. Poor service and average food.

Quick service. Arrived on Sunday at 7pm with queue but turnover service is fast.
Good quality Japanese food at reasonable price.
Service is attentive but I feel not personal as staff were quite clumsy, hence deduct 1 star.
Where I was seated at, very sticky floors.

Skipping the queue with early dinner. Reach here at about 4.30pm and order the claypot rice, San Lou Fried Bee Hoon and salted egg butter gourd. The taste is good overall but not the claypot rice, perhaps more salted fish needs to be added to make it more flavourful.
tasty food, gd service (‚Äù treat others the way you wanted to be treated‚Äù )
Small Japanese Restaurant in Tai Seng.  We ordered a Truffle beef don and a Bara Chirashi.  The beef is great, tender and tasty.  The Chirashi is good as well.

Hashida Private Dining.
Chef Hatch is having his pop up restaurant here at OUE Social kitchen in a casual cozy setting.
- We had the Omakase course and I sort of lost count on the number of times that was served üòÜ
- Service by his crew was impeccable, with little details well taken care of.
- We were very well pampered and I made sure I booked my spot for next month before leaving üëçüèº

Very bad. Had the three meat grilled spaghetti dish. The waiting time was the horrid - we had two gelato and we told three different staff (including the manager) that they can serve but we waited for 20 minutes and we just left cos we couldn't wait longer ...
I ordered penang laksa, looks more like vegetarian laksa instead. Soup is ok, taste sour and spicy, but the toppings only had lettuce, cucumber and onion. At $4, not really worth the price.
potatoes were cooked really nicely and their malatang tastes gud!
Consistently good food. Value for money. Pleasant service.
Chicken cutlet with aglio olio
Not to our liking.
The steak is done well and grilled over fire. Very worth the dollar.
Not fresh
Good! Very healthy! Suitable for old people.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Love it..

The authentic Indian food...

You can find the one of the best north Indian food in Singapore..
Friendly and super accommodating. Coffee was too sweet and instantly made a new one to my taste

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Crispy prata. And I really mean crispy prata. Even the egg prata is crispy.

While their food is good, the service is sorely wanting. They are not friendly and don't know manners. They can't smile and they serve the customer just like a robot. An attitude and gratitude change will help.

Malaysia Hawker delights! Authentic Ipoh taste and Penang style delights! Love the hor fon prawn and chicken noodles. Love the unique Ipoh aroma white coffees. Love that relaxing spacious lounges well decorated for nostalgic Malaysia Kampong atmosphere and warm services. Freshly prepared healthy ingridients with tender loving caring skillful cooking and professional authentic skills. Get the taste when cannot go to Malaysia. Friendly cosy comfy ambience for romantic intimates groups students tourists & families.

I enjoy the variety of food choices and the service. Salmon was abit dry but still good. Only down side is we had to pay via the app before our order comes. So if you need to add any other order you need to separately pay again...
Prata is good and yummy.  They have just renovated the place and looks cleaner with more seating capacity.  Assortment of drinks and Indian Muslim food.  Price seem to be higher after renovation.

Service has improved. Cleanliness too. Now at Kids stop near Science Center. Prices have increased a bit. But still not bad at all.

The food is very good. A great authentic  "India" Indian restaurant in Singapore. Generally this is how food is in India compared to what we get in Prata places and local restaurants in Singapore.
Nice fragrant chicken rice. Tender chicken pieces. The bundled meals are value for money. Chili adds a punch
nice food and chill place to have dinner with your family, friends and loved ones! will come back for more and hopefully desserts and live band will be available the next time round üôèüôèüôè

This is a good find for me. Chicken and fried fish had nice tasty seasoning. Rice is fragrant, but a bit too soft to my ideal. The only thing that I'm not fond of is the chilli, different type than usual nasi lemak chilli

Excellent service - Staffs were friendly and gave good recommendations.
Good ambience - Spacious and comfortable.

Ate there around 2pm today. Fortunately found a parking nearby. Last slot! Parking is not so easily available here.

Has mutton murtabak and teh halia ‚Äòkao‚Äô. By default it will come with mutton curry. Asked for fish curry. Both curry is top notch. Had tried this place a few times and the curry is always top notch!

The teh halia is also very nice! Strong ginger and tea flavour.

The mutton murtabak is nice but I prefer the dough to be fried until crispy and it is not üòÇüòÇ. So the 4 stars.

Updated 23rd Jan 2022.
We went there for dinner today. All the food flavor is spot on and the texture of the various prata crispy and nice. The mee goreng also has nice wok hei. However, all of them was overly salty. The salt overpowered the rest of the flavor so definitely a minus point. So after today's experience, dropped to 3 stars.

It's quite an old establishment. When we went there, there was some event going on and book the whole place and no restaurant reception so we found it strange and confusing since we also booked a table for family reunion dinner. After much trouble, they allocated us to rooms behind. Not a good start. Food was normal. Service was normal. Will I come again? Probably not.

Their Mee Rebus is one of their signature dish you must absolutely try. The noodles were coated with thick aromatic potato gravy, which was so good that would leave you craving for another bowl. Definitely worth to queue and try.

I ordered this morning some poori and it was good together with the side dish of potatoe.
I ordered again this evening Poori together with mee goreng.
However the mee goreng was too saltish..

Good place for an introduction to Mexican food. A little pricey but flavours are strong and good. Nachos and fries are great. Unfortunately they do not have salsa here so the strong acidity and spice is missing
So so food.
Despite its name Grille Factory, this place does not make window/door grilles. They grill meat.
Not a big fan of veg food but this place surprised me.  The star dishes were the abacus and cod fish. Looks and taste great!
Highly recommended, and probably one of the better Sichuan cuisines in Singapore. Very authentic and the Ê∞¥ÁÖÆÁâõËÇâ is really tasty. I will definitely go again. Worth the extra mile! üëç

The female staff mending the cashier was really rude. No matter how good or how affordable the food is, if the attitude of the staff is rotten then its a shop that i wouldn't even think of visiting. If the owner of the shop is viewing this review, i hope changes could be implemented to the staff before placing them at the shopfront. I feel that the branding of the store really suits the way she acts as she is simply MAD when it comes to customer service.

A rare sight to see pork tomahawk steak in a coffee shop western stall as usually they are only sold in cafes or restaurants. The sauce is great and the huge meat is tender. Comes with crispy waffle fries, salad and mashed potato. Highly recommended!

Mala hotpot, inexpensive, can try.

Good service, fast n spicy

CASH ONLY place (as of Apr 2018, accept cards). The signature gyoza has both ends open (wrapped only in the middle). The boiled dumplings would have a small amount of soup in it. Do try their fried red bean paste cake. One of the best gyozas in town favored by many Japanese.

17/06/18
Better than average family restaurant. This restaurant has been around for more than 20 years. It is famous for their San Lau Hor fan. Assam Fish Head is good. This restaurant is worth trying.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Spacious.Like the Alfresco dining.Onion pratas. Must ask for less sugar for tea tarik.Meehoon goreng too saltfish. love. iced limau on hot day. refreshing
Always love their Heng Hwa Bee Hoon. Lunch promo has 20% off all items in main menu, very worth it!
Place is small. The place is a bit stuffy.
Nice food

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Still like e San Lou Hor Fun, end up drive further to take away ...can try grab food too...enjoy then
Friendly staff, delicious foods, affordable price. Very nice staff lady offer me more chilies since the food is not spicy for my taste bud. Highly reccomended.

Came on a weekday evening. Place was almost full but fortunately we could still get a table. Had the chicken biryani and felt the portion is rather small now as compared tp years ago, but I find it is rather suitable now for one person unless you are a heavy eater. There is quite a variety of food here but we didn't try much this time round.
This keuh was nice and chewy. The rest like goreng pisang and ondeh ondeh, were so so.

The waiting was very long, but the food was good.   The salmons with the veg, seems like a balance diet with rice and soup with fruits too.

Try to avoid meals times. Their staffs are friendly too. Business too good. Just imagine, queuing to make payment also waited about 15 min. A typical Saturday evening.

The food was well done, with an authentic Cantonese flair. Some dishes to look out for would be their roast meat platter and spiced dumplings.

Service was adequate, but the place is usually swamped in the evenings, with long wait times and poorer service. At times it felt like the place was understaffed. The service staff made do with the manpower they had however, and did their best to make the dining experience enjoyable.

Would definitely recommend having a meal here if authentic Cantonese cuisine is what you are looking for.
Not bad western not the best but still good reasonable priced tasted not bad

My family and I was craving for prata. We ate few times but today‚Äôs experience was horrible. Upon reaching a table, there‚Äôs an ipad left on the table beside the table we are located. I partially open the cover of ipad and check if someone has left it, but I decided to move it away from our table and leave it. About 15mins later a Lady confronted us and say next time dont touch, ask around and thats how she reserved the table. She talked to us in a bad tone. We apologised and keep quiet. The mentioned lady was apparently working in the shop. After few minutes, a guy, who is working also in the shop, talked to us and said ‚Äúwhat she said was right? Do you have something to say?‚Äù Then we defend ourselves. They embarrassed us in front of many people which is not a customer service. To the owner of this shop, may review the cctv and investigate on the incident. A belonging that is valuable shouldnt be left unattended. Such behaviour is unacceptable for customer service. A proper and mannerly approach should be considered. Hope you can take action on this.

Their rice was fluffy and there was a strong coconut+pandan aroma, which I liked it very much. The chilli sauce is sweet and not spicy. I‚Äôve also added on fishcake and begedil but the portion was so small. Chicken wing was tasty and flavourful but the winner here for me was still the rice. üò¨

I visited on Saturday around 6pm and the place was packed. The food came about 15 minutes after ordering. Overall the pratas were good compared to coffeeshop standards, the only complaint I have is that some part of the prata is hard(like a biscuit).

Service of the staff not so good, they just put the dish on the table quickly and dropped the utensils on the plate and left quickly... Ur staff could have just placed it nicely instead of dropping the utensils on the plate.

Hidden at one corner in the cafeteria of Jackson Square, this is a rare gem and one which you want to keep for life (I'm not exaggerating). Try it and you will know the definition of value-for-money, which is somewhat an understatement. A more apt description might just be optimal consumer satisfaction for every cent incurred. Putting the heavenly food quality and generous portion aside, service standards by the cashier may likely put some restaurants out there to shame. If you are down to your last 10 bucks in life, you've gotta save it for this.

Food is delicious and served in good portions. Huge variety and value for money! Not forgetting excellent and friendly service from Lisa! My family and I enjoy our time at the dinner buffet very much.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Good place for south Indian meals.
Humble people along with tasty food options. Priced considerably lower as well.
They sell marvellous foods...

(Translated by Google) Poor food

Various options of food, isn't overly crowded during weekday lunch hour
Western food options - good to have for a change. But no fight against the deep fried chicken wings in the same food court

Used to really love the thai food here like about a year ago(?) but things have changed right now and this place is really not worth a visit anymore! Would totally give it a 0 stars if I could. Recently visited the restaurant and all I can say is bad service and bad quality food. Standards have really dropped like no tommorow. So focused on delivery that they literally neglect the dine in customers, food took over an hour to come(and its not even all the food we ordered coming at once), literally had to cancel order half way because the waiting time was just getting way too long and the staffs were not even apologetic at all. (terrible balance between deliveries and dine in customers if cannot balance just off your deliveries gosh) Adding on restaurant definitely has some hygiene issues, place where food comes out is also place for return plates also saw staff touching some of the vegetable with their hands while placing the sauce. Terrible!!!! would not recommend at all if you want authentic thai food.

Old fashion zi char place, crowded 2 days before CNY, guess many are having shou gong fan there.

The ambient is ok, normal coffee shop style, just much bigger in space.

The dishes order were mostly tasty, except salted fish sprouts (which I didn‚Äôt spot any salted fish) and braised tofu (which didn‚Äôt look or taste super appetising).

Nevertheless, recommend three egg spinach, herbal chicken (the soup was really good), wok hey hor fan!

We have Ordered naan and roti items with Panner makhani, pepper mutton, kudal masala. Not worth for money.

Pepper mutton more oily and salty
Kudal masala over salty
Panner makhani also average taste.
Overall not good dinner experience and taste.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Great Northern Chinese cuisine! Crystal Jade is a well-known chain in Singapore and the Toa Payoh branch lives up to expectations. The service was fast and friendly, and the food was tasty and fresh.  A guarantee.
Nice food and nice view! And very amazing prize for a whole set at only 14 dollars . Will definitely visit again with my future girl friend ( if I have hahaha )

Went there on 18Apr 7pm. Penang Char Kuay Teow were dry and light in colour and not dark. Not much taste . Price not worth to pay for as little items in the Char Kuay Teow. Not really authentic as claim from Penang.

Firstly, it was long queue during dinner time, so the expectation was got very high.    The food was ok and hot pot quite good. The value was deducting from utensils didn‚Äôt supply. When waitress finish my order, then she didn‚Äôt supply utensils to us, that is after our meals arrived. we request from the service table. Secondly, the waiters is supply wrong meal frequently. The worst is there have two big fly surrounding, feel so unhygienic.
Ordered the dry banmian ($4.50) and requested more chillies. It turned out salty but not spicy at all. The popiah ($2.50) so so only and cendol ($2.50) was tasteless and diluted.
Quick bites...good for kids

Such a beautiful place to dine in, with the playlist being on point all the time. Everything we had was so good, left the place with a happy tummy. Received a wonderful service from Mr Ash from the Windsledt outlet. We had a few food on the house and left the place with more freebies. Talk about a company that believes in the more you give, the more you'll receive. Wont hesitate to come back again!
Food taste almost authentic to those i had in china

Ordered cereal prawn, broccoli scallop & 2 chili crabs with a seafood soup. Didn't manage to criticize any of the dishes. All dishes of the taste found spot on and waitress was single handling the ground in well manner. Lastly, the rice was quality. Expandable future.
Wonderful non veg food and cheap
Cheap no frills favourites from Malaysia. Claypot rice has got the burnt rice bits but missing out on the salted fish.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
Lots of good food options within the hawker and around the area too. Food are all on the second floor with the wet Market downstairs. Home to many famous food like hokkien mee (come daiky- my go to alternative to geylang), fishball noodle, chicken rice and more.  Tried a new peanut pancake here today (stall is located in the middle area) and was cheap and good ! Pieces were also quite big.

There's a good hakka ytf at the nearby coffee shop and a couple of cafes near the old creamier  area.

My go to place if I'm around the tpy area for a relaxing fuss free meal. Lots of parking options around too.

Affordable local style western food that's value for money. Great taste, reasonable pricing, super friendly and pretty lady boss. Recently they also adopted contactless payment via SGQR so you don't have to fumble with cash (and more hygienic during this covid season)

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Long queue despite restaurant being half full; queued more than an hour to be seated. Then waited another 40 mins for food to arrive. Standard of food has dropped. I have been a supporter of Aston's but not anymore after this experience.

As a Shanghainese, I am very satisfied with their fried buns and xiao long bao, it is the taste of my hometown. And I am sure only they offers pork string in Singapore. I will visit them again with my children in the coming school holidays.
Really nice Hakka food. They feel like home food and very affordable for a restaurant.

Not sure if this is authentic yunnan rice noodles. But it sure taste good for me. The soup base is full of flavor, noodles texture are just right. And the rest of the add on ingredients are fresh and good.

Super awesome meal I had that other day on the 22nd of June. Was serve by a young lady. Rice bowls are awesome, tried one stick of grill initially, but it was way too good. Tea was free flow, like most Singaporean free thing must take. in conclusion, food 10/10 waiting time 9/10(Not so busy day afterall), customer service, 9/10. Will definitely visit again
Tried the A5 Wagyu n double karubi. I prefer the karubi set for its value. Jyo karubi especially

order a triple meat grill. and seafoods marinara with ice cream and ice lemon tea
triple meat grill - beef cut is quite bad with thick layer of inedible. chicken not grilled enough .  sausage is very basic . i would say it is a decent dish that shall be priced at 15-18 instead of 20+
the food not hot as it was serve together with the pasta .
seafood marinara - the ingredients is fresh and generous. only issue is the sauce too watery.
ice lemon tea - very normal concentrate taste
ice cream- is call gelato but taste like normal marigold ice cream

be prepared to spend some time for waiting food . is not as fast as usual western cuisine.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: Went for Easter brunch there excellent Cantonese cuisine and pretty reasonable pricing with great ambience and the service is fast and good üëçüëçüëç

I had high expectations for this restaurant, but it was not as good I thought. The place was noisy, and the food was low quality. For example, when I ordered pineapple rice, I expected rice with pineapple, but turned out to be yellow pineapple flavoured rice. However, the drinks were quite yummy. It only took about 6 minutes for our food to be served. My overall opinion about this restaurant is that it is noisy, the food is ok, and it is usually crowded.

Today went over this place for lunch but we do not have a menu to look at and make our order. The staff told us only one menu is available and it was place at the ordering counter. When we are looking at the menu, the queue started and the staff told us to put the menu back for those who are in queue to place order. Later the staff told us to scan the QR code to place our order. I just wondering if old people doesn't know how to use phone to scan QR code to place order then no need to order. Besides how can such a eatery just print one miserable menu. Perhaps they just want to cater to young patrons. Furthermore the auntie taking the order also very bad attitude as though we own her money. Their food taste wasn't to my liking. For sure this will be the first n last time patron this eatery.
Tender beef! Great quality for the competitive price. Staff is not that friendly but no complaints for the price.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Our second time here, this time round we only had some snacks and drink.

Overall food both times are yummy and prices are ok too. Though I would love the Ginger Tea (Teh Haliah) to have more kick ü§™ it is a bit on the lower taste.
Excellent food and service

Not bad the food, definitely not as good as what you can get in Penang. But good enough for me to want to go back when crave for the char kuey teow. The cendol was nice too with gula Melaka. The Âçó‰π≥ÁÇ∏ËÇâworth a try too
The Famous Irish Rosted Duck Very Juicee , is to die for, have to try it. Have 2 Souce, Plum Souce is 5 Star, and Sweet and Sour Pork Excellen. Best Service by Alan. üòäüëçüëçüëçüëçüëç‚ú®Ô∏è
Authentic veg restaurant. Good family restaurant. I suggest this restaurant for indian breakfast recipes
Food is really good! But price is quite steep! Nice  Veranda setup.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: This is one of the must try in vision exchange serving authentic Indian food. Tried the butter chicken naan which is alot for a normal lunch. For light eaters, I will recommend it for sharing. Complete the meal with Masala Tea or Teh Tarik. The cost of a set like this is about $12.
The rojaks speechless,superb.And the gravy...need no introduction.

Got mee rebus satay, mee siam, 2 chicken wings and coffee for $17.70. Food is mediocre and pricey. The absolute downer is the workers allow people to cut queue. There was a lot of confusion about the queue and the workers allow their regulars/friends to cut queue. Even while I was eating, the queue confusion continued. For goodness sake, put up some poles, signs and lines to clear the confusion.
Friendly staff! The food was good and it is a nice change from the food in NTU
Well marinated, juicy and soft for Hot Plate Steak, worth to wait and fast servings.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
The food is nice and delicious plus the green chilli sauce wen u dip the food very spicy cool the place quite relaxing üëç
Recommend
Nice chicken chop set. The chicken is cooked nicely with juicy meat and crispy skin.

We came at around 8.30pm to 9pm on a weekday evening and were surprised that we were allowed to still come in for a meal this late.  The food came quickly.  The chili spiciness was just nice - unlike some places that make your eyes water just by looking at the dish.  The dishes are a bit sweet, but that seems to be how Thai food is.  The atmosphere was relaxed and we didn't feel hurried to leave even though it was late.  Great service from YiXin and Sue.  Thank you very much for being so accommodating and friendly.
service is really slow here and sometimes i order the rice bowl it comes cool..
prices for rojak is INSANE !! squid and lungs priced at the size of the item ! 1 small squid + 1 small lungs + 3 empty dough + 1 fish fillet & a can of coke cost SGD 19 !!

Had prata,impossible rogan josh,takeway impossible mee goreng.
Prata was ok standard,impossible rogan josh was very good gravy was thick smooth taste was very delighful.
But the mee goreng was was big let down there was this smell the chye sim was green yellow dry at rottening stage the sauce was spoil and impossible meat was nowhere to be seen.Had to throw away it was impossible to eat.

Great food but a tad too costly. going through the menu u will find prices x2 x3 x4 of usual prices. I personally thought twice about many dishes that I would have love to try. I would frequent if the cost is a bit more reasonable.

Want compliment 2 servers name sally/Aying  both are really good performance and efficient even shop are busy üëçüëçüëç need give extra bonus . Btw foods are delicious.  Me and husband recommend TPY outlets , we will come back to eat üëç
Service has always been friendly and personal. Curry chicken is worth going for on a damp weekday evening .
Good western food.

Came on a Sunday night, many tables filled. Expected the food to take a longer time as the place was packed. Food arrived a lot quicker than expected. Probz 10mins from ordering.
Food is value for money.
The star of the meal (for me) was the fish head fried with bitter gourd.
Minced pork tofu with chai poh was a miss.
the cadyceps (?) soup was the highlight. very very good. the rest not too memorable

Seriously, the staff are very rude. I was looking forward to a happy good meal but the staff‚Äô attitude denied me the wish.
(Actually, not even one star becos the staff‚Äôs attitude sabotaged the nice food experience). The whole team needs to be replaced soonest.
Been A Few Times There. Tried The Rosti And Taste Great As Well. Mushroom Soup Creamy With Lots Of Mushroom Bits. Affordable Western Food Worth To Try.

Standards have dropped and service standards as well. Waiter didn‚Äôt bother to ask when dessert should be served , and dishes came out so fast that it felt like they were rushing you to eat faster and go. Dessert was served when we were not ‚Ä¶

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Ordered via grab and my roasted duck noodles had NO DUCK! üò§
Tasteless horfun and ee mee. Worst ee mee ever eaten! Went to buy after reading review... but totally disappointed! Will never go again!

Nice food with good dipping sauces but setting in an industrial park canteen or food centre is not very condusive as it gets pretty hot & sweaty which is actually how it should be but may not be very well received by people here.
Pork bbq wasn‚Äôt bad. Ramen was soso only. I think bishan also got same stall, when I ordered deliver from that one was better.

A hidden gem in the neighbourhood with a wide selection of western/nepalese food. It has been around for more than a decade, and the owner is very friendly. Food quality was way better than Jack's Place and prices were very reasonable!

Some bad stuff tho:

1. The pizza we ordered was a bit too small and tasted like it came from Cold Storage.

2. Mashed potato tasted like it came from a powdered packet

3. Service was very very slow on a crowded Sunday and we had to set aside more than an hour for lunch.

I think service might be much better on quieter weekdays.
Good food and polite smiley staff. Opens 24hour.
Love the great variety of hawker food that are value for money and great tasting too! Definitely will revisit soon!
Quality ramen at affordable prices. Loved their chashu, it is flavourful and has a great texture. The broth is not overly salty as well, would suit people who prefers a lighter broth like me.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: If you are looking for cheap and best food option then go for Anjana Kitchen walkable from Jurong East MRT. I had Tandoori Naan Set, it was tasty & cheaper.

Food's delicious! Their signature duck and pork in the bun is amazingly good. The rest of the food that we ordered were good as well, but it was the duck that melted in my mouth and keeps me dreaming of the next time I go back.

I think they served an extra appetiser (fried fish skin) that was crisp, tasty, but still light.

We were seated all the way in a corner, so, sometimes it was hard to signal to the wait staff, but otherwise, food is great. I think the external seating is just for the Lunar New Year festivities, as it doesn't look permanent.
Freshly made delicious food with a nice nod to local palette. Good people with excellent service.

Located just 5mins+ walk from Potong Pasir MRT, Gu Ma Jia serves a decent varieties of local ÁÖÆÁÇí that are simple yet delicious.

The Assam Groupa Fish Head was quite spicy and goes very well with rice. Kyoto pork ribs were very tender with appetising sweet and sour sauce. Salted egg prawns were very fresh but otherwise pretty normal. What surprise me was the ying yang kai lan which was served with deep fried shredded kai lan leaves and crunchy kai lan stems.

Staff were very prompt in service and  friendly as well. Recommended to make reservations during Friday night and weekend to avoid not being able to get seats. Pricing were reasonable as well.

Overall definitely one of the better zi char restaurants option in Singapore.

There are plenty of dessert cafe and bar next to it for after meal chilling sessions as well.
great service and pasta is v tasty!
Nice food and reasonable price. Worth a little wait as Seller is OMO.
Have a good variety of dishes to select. Great food and ambiance.
Food is so so other than the famous Henghua mee Hoon. Price is at high side. We were asked to share table with others! Don‚Äôt think it is right when we r in phase 2 now
Taste good. Small place but cosy. Shop person very pleasant.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: The food was ok but the waiting time it can be work it out!
Decent priced steak and taste good too. Love the pulled pork burger. The beer and cider are rather well priced at $6+ we will come back again. Last order at 8.30pm.

(Translated by Google) Came here for the first time, every dish is delicious üòã
The dishes are hot, very satisfied üòç

The food are delicious and the price are really low. For example a packet of Nasi lemak only cost $1.00. In the morning store might be pack with workers buying breakfast

Big bowl of soup and noodles as expected from yun nan ËøáÊ°•Á±≥Á∫øÔºåit has its own twist which is the chrysanthemum. And do beware because it has a layer of oil it keeps the soup hot so when its first served to you, blow to allow it to cool down first before you sip it.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: First time visiting this neighbourhood mookata. Food is tasty, it's air-conditioned, prices are reasonable. But to be expected, it was massively overcrowded when we visited on a Saturday night--staff was running around all over the place trying to handle orders, customers were getting impatient, etc. We also ended up with stomach aches the day after, so can't say much about food hygiene. First and last visit.

During term time alot of students placing order. Note that when I tried to order using Grab, the shop was "closed". So thinking of picking up your order? Nah. I also realised that children's Happy Meal is not available here. üòê

Came in due to curiosity. Regretted it. I think the cooking style and taste is just not our style. Most are overcooked and average tasting. I totally did not like the pan fried glutinous rice. Too hard and sticks to the teeth.

April 2022
Price increase to $9.80 for oyster omelette. Oysters are smaller too.

Ordered olive fried rice. Didn‚Äôt really like it as I prefer savoury taste more than sweet (some floss on top. Sweet taste there) and the rice seem sweet too.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî-
Green curry with rice (don‚Äôt remember price) and oyster omelette $9. Good taste.
Small portion but still 10/10 , says smth about quality over quantity ü§©

Horrible takeaway experience today.
Hear me out and I will explain.

I was there to order 2 plain and 1 egg prata at around 4.15pm. There were only one other male customer dining in at that time.

The female cashier kept on asking me whether I want crispy. I found it weird that she asked but nevertheless said yes. She asked a few more times to confirm and I said "of course I want crispy". I even said "if you have freshly made, why not?" And she never replied. By the way, tell me who doesn't want crispy prata, Right? And it also insinuate freshly made right?

But upon receiving the bill, I noticed I was charged 10 cent more for each prata. I quickly took a glance at the menu board above my head and realized I was charged the prata made of wholegrain.

At that moment, I knew I was cheated. Why did she not use the word 'wholegrain' in the communication? It was an outright lie to get people to buy the wholegrain prata when she said 'crispy'.

I confirmed with her whether she meant wholegrain when she said crispy and she admitted.

Even though it was only 30 cents more in total to get the 3 wholegrain pratas compared to getting the normal ones, but that wasn't what I initially wanted.

And because I'm rushing to fetch my daughter from school, I decided not to argue anymore.

It is so disappointing that the staff lied to sell the wholegrain prata which I assume might not be popular with the general public and probably trying to improve her own sales. It was plain dishonesty.

Please guys, this is a true story.. don't fall into the 'crispy' trap.
5 star for the prata

Had the braised intestine vermicelli Á∫¢ÁÉßËÇ•ËÇ†Á±≥, the intestine was soft and well braised, no funky smell or whatsoever, vermicelli was soft and silky unlike our local thick bee hoon. Soup might look spicy but it's not, the colour was from the braising sauce of the intestine.
Excellent hawker foods in coffeeshop very popular right next to wet market with very delicious nasi lemak cheap and good value for money and friendly service.
My favourite chicken cutlet with french fries + rice!!!!! the highlight of my day whenever i come to school. Thank you for the friendly service
Economical meals
Nice Chinese food in neighbourhood area. Always crowded during weekends. Located in ITE Central.
Amazing old school western food, portion was generous and food very delicious.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
one of the worst buffet ever.

2 paying adults can only order 1 x scoop of ice cream and prawn/crayfish.

Stingy af policy, most of the items on the menu comes with rice or noodles that is served compulsory.

Order takes long to come and staff needs many reminder to get it right.

1/10 star would not try again.

Long queue at 9am on weekends. The handmade fish ball/cake is really nice. The dry noodle has special chilli sauce and fried lard. Worth a try if staying nearby. The boss is friendly even though he is busy, such good attitude is hard to find among stalls with good business nowadays.
After a breezy stroll at the Gardens by the bay... Yummy! Had a really tasty Roti John smashed with generous amount of chilli and mayo. üòãüòãüòã
Great place! Coconut jelly must try!
Mutton soup with lots of veggies. Perfect as simple lunch or dinner. Highly recommended

A couple of Sundays ago, after playing mahjong at the inlaws place and losing close to $40, it was time for dinner.
We decided to try the Thai restaurant, Siam Kitchen, which we had not eaten at before.
Placed our order for an appetiser platter and a seabass set. We got the glass of Thai milk tea that came with the set but was told we don't get SAFRA member discount with that set meal and so no discount for the meal. Disapppointing. üòü Just as well that we didn't order dessert which looks to me was overpriced. Ended up spending about the same amount I lost at mahjong earlier.
The soup with meatball was served with the baked potato. The baked potato still tasted OK but the soup was too salty for me so I didn't like it.
The appetiser platter had a lot of food. I guessed it can be filling enough for a full meal for some people.
The seabass was last to serve. The taste was OK but not something I'd missed enough to come back for more.
The place wasn't crowded throughout. Diners came and left while we were there and the number of groups was more or the less the same before and after our meal.
Better option for dessert was McDonald's which was less than 50m away.

It was my first visit.
Service can be improved. It was hard to get the attention of a staff to take our orders as serving staffs do not take orders.
Everything went well until my Tsukune came uncooked in the center. I felt disgusted because I already took a big bite.
They did replace my tsukune but I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll visit again. Their service recovery weren‚Äôt the best.

Wow so much controversies. I like the food. Highlights are the charred char siew and roast meat. The meal pictured was about $38, for 3 pax. Was lucky as the crowd wasn't bad on Sunday 12pm. They served the food very quickly. Will be back again if there isn't any queue. Nice food though slightly ex.

I love how they deep fried the potato slices and scrambled the eggs. For someone that cannot really take spice, xiao la was a little too spicy for me‚Ä¶ but it was worth it. It was very fragrant instead of just spicy. POTATOES & EGGS are a MUST order.
For this bowl, it was $30.

While we enjoy the food, the establishment hasn't moved ahead along with the Government's reviewed measures that customers do not need to rescan the silly 'safe entry' when it's already been done at the shopping mall's main entrances. Please keep up with times and do away with this silly hassle.

Mr Alan who served us is a professional staff. He made good recommendations to the food and was not pushy to make us over order. He continued to serve us with excellent service throughout. Overall the dining experience was awesome. Good customer service, good food.
Damn shiok fried stuff!! Curry puffs are pretty good as well.

Great place, excellent food! I was quite surprise that with such delicious Thai food, there wasn‚Äôt a crowd!

This is my second time visiting this place. They have different level of spiciness; local, Thai and super Thai. I went with the local version. Unlike many Thai food restaurants, their flavour will change with the spice level but this one maintains the flavour irregardless of the spice level.

The only downside is the fish. Tried twice based on different cooking style I guess they have still some rooms for improvement. Mind you, the fish is fresh and soft but I prefer it abit more crispy (deep fried fish fillet) and prefer a stronger flavour for chilli and lime fillet. Oh yes, you can choose either to order whole fish or fillet which many stalls doesn‚Äôt give this option.

I would still go back and try many of their other dishes because price for the food quality is a steal. Plus don‚Äôt have to queue to get a seat :)

Decent prata and iced milo, however the murtabak is too dry. Long queues for a seat but it moves quickly. It‚Äôs a good idea to walk off the calories after a heavy meal. Will try it for supper sometime.

I have been ordering from them via grab food multiple times. I always order the Ribeye Steak Set. Tbh for food court western, this really tastes delicious and the portions are sufficient. I don't know about the rest of the items on the menu cause I've never tried it  but their ribeye steak has never disappointed me.
Good place to hangout with friends and family, variety choices of food

Miserable food, lousy taste, extremely small portion and poor service. Takes more than 20 mins on average to serve up a dish. This is preposterous that such quality is served. To be frank if I can choose to input zero star, I definitely would.

Nice vegetarian food. Not exactly healthy but definitely tasted good when dining in compared to our previous delivery order.

But I think they are quite understaffed. Quite hard to get the staff‚Äôs attention.

Good location - will be back

Went there during lunch time and I was a bit disappointed with the food. I ordered the plaster blaster, prata Alfredo and Iced Teh Tarik. The plaster blaster was a disaster, I ate there multiple times and this time was the worst. The prata was cold and the taste just don't mixed well especially with a cold prata. The prata Alfredo however taste much more delicious and filled with cheese and every bite is so good. Just make you want to keep eating. But to end off, the Iced Teh Tarik was so diluted that drinking plain water was much better. Overall the food service kinda of dropped, maybe it is due to the lack of manpower and proper management but the food is suppose to be unique and delicious. Hope it will improve over time again to be back to where it was previously.

This bowl may look small, but when you pour it out on the plate, the serving was quite huge! I can‚Äôt finish the entire serving. Did I mention it was very yummy and fresh? Came back to try their mentaiko salmon. Super good as well!

I have been eating Shami for as long as I‚Äôve been residing in Yishun for 20+ years. All i can say imo is they increase prices along the way and inflation is real (which is fine with me as idm paying for good food) but the quality of their product (ie. rice/spices/size of their expensive meat or fishes) is really getting worse. Really disappointing. Today shall be the last time i‚Äôm patronizing them at NPC outlet.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
Best so far and they have not shut down but relocated a few units away within the food centre; from 01-10 to 01-32.

01-10 now sells Chinese Food

Nice food, experience and services at PUTIEN. The staff were attentive and served tea to us. Sweet and sour pork and the fish was yummy. It was quite warm so the staff gave us a small fan, great service!

This store used to be decent before covid. Its standards were already dropping in 2019 but decided to give it a try again.

Rice had no coconut taste and fragrance and was dry. Food ingredients were barely warm and nothing spectacular. Expensive too.

Hopefully can relook at what went wrong in the last few years..

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Had a good dinner here with my family. They only had white chicken left though as we came pretty late ( around 8pm), so do come early if you're eyeing the roasted chicken or roasted pork. Ordered some sides as well,overall quite nice for the variety it has in addition to some pretty good chicken rice.

Quaint little authentic store below a HDB. Not very accessible by public transport. Bosses and chef are Shanghainese. Do give them a call before coming to make reservations as the crowd is very unpredictable to prevent disappointment ü•≤

Flavours wise everything is freaking amazing. ü§©

Would HIGHLY RECOMMEND the vegetable spring rolls and pan fried buns. Would say portion wise is really small. But it's good enough not to over eat. Average cost per dish is $6.

Complimentary homemade Chinese chrysanthemum tea w no sugar inside in a huge flask üòç really feels so homey I love it ü•∞

Soup makes the ramen overall taste good. However serving-wise not very 'King'-like. Little serving of soup for takeaway order, more like sauce, half the ramen showing above the broth. Half an ajitama egg non-marinated, no flavor if consumed without soup. 2-small slices chasu, taste pretty good. The good tasting broth saved the dish overall. (Edit: Ordered Tonkotsu Ramen)

Friendly staff and great Malay food.
Must try their chilly sauce. They have a few type for different type of food. Spicy hot. Price is a bit pricey but really worth the price if you look at the serving of the meats per order.

We came here to celebrate dad birthday. The food quality is excellent. The staffs are very polite and extremely helpful. They are always smiling, checking in on quality of food, changing plates. The restaurant has a nice and unique atmosphere. Definitely will come again.

It says Swee Choon Express. It should be called Swee Choon Slow. I waited for 15 min for two orders of pao. They should not have the word 'Express' for the amk branch so as to manage customers expectation. I recommend that you make your order then go for a walk at the hub then return to collect.

Quality of food doesn't match the price. They charge whatever they want. Sometime they charge you $6.50 for chicken meal and then next time they will charge you $10.50.

They serve wrong bill and the customer need to ask them to correct it multiple times to match the rate shown on the menu cards
Now they had a promotion if order value above $30, free kids menu set

The lamb shank is very tender.
Nasi briyani rice has flavour there. Was a bit lukewarm.

For $8 the lamb shank meal is a great steal, if not for the rice i would have given it 5 star.

Feedback to the lady boss... she was very responsive. Will check out quality consistency 2nd time
oh .. great and yummy foods üòò. salmon are fresh and juicy. foods portion just nice for sharing. serving staffs are helpful.
With that kind of price, you can have better western food elsewhere.
Nasi Lemak surprisingly good. Egg yolk perfect, wings crispy, and with teh halia cost less than $5
This place never disappoints. Chicken is fresh, rice is fragrant.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content:
Pleasantly surprised, never thought such good Indian fare could be found in the heartlands.
- Plain dosai, fried crispy was delicious.  appropriately fermented, though a little greasier than I liked.
- Mutton stew grossly under-marketed.  Super delicious...why it is obscured with zero description and photos is anyone's guess.
- Rawa dosai was a little over peppered but still ok.
- Iced tea-O was too sweet.  both the regular and less-sweet versions were way too sweet.  better with 50% sugar.
- Service was an issue.  While everyone was friendly and efficient,  our server wiped our table (when clearing the dishes) with our USED wet ones.  This is highly unhygienic, and potentially a hazard to both himself and the next patron. He did not appear to return to wipe with another cloth or spray cleaner on the table.  Because of this, we deduct a star.
I love the carrot cake, traditional and not greasy at all. Well presented. It will be my new hangout.
My 4th time here and I ALWAYS order the fish maw soup. Usually busy so customer service might take awhile but the staffs are friendly and nice. Good for an old school taste.
Love the chicken chop here. It has the grilled flavor that you don't get in other coffeeshop western stalls

Ordered Egg Fried Rice with Pork Chop and Prawn Pan Fried Buns. Pork chop definitely pre-cooked, froze and re-heated. So it is mushy and without the usual meat fibre texture. The egg fried rice has no wok-hey at all. The dish is bad. For the buns, the filling tastes ok but the skin is way too thick and doughy. I think they used the wrong type of flour or rather the flour mix is not good. Overall, food is bad and totally not worth the money.

Went AMK HUB Fair Price shopping and came across Malaysia Boleh, decided to try out.  The Kalng Bak Gut Teh is very nice, highly recommended. Clay pot chicken is not the best I have try. Chendol is tasty too, have the authentic Melaka taste,  quite crowded on the Sunday Afternoon.
Just try the italian herb fried rice is really very good

Charging for water at a restaurant is a total put off for me.
Unfortunately, I have placed my food orders.
Add to your food cost, because not all will will looked at your 50 cents hidden on your haddock or duck.
Food was good, no complaints except your salad was not fresh.

Some of the prominent differences are :

1. The materials  especially the chicken is very fresh.

2. The blend of spices in the soup is perfect.

3. The portions of chicken is generous and not OVERLY Cooked. So it's very SOFT, TENDER & SUCCULENT .

So the combination is thus  perfect and they have also  successfully RETAINED a home cooked touch.

In the past I've a Malay friend from Kuala Lumpur who came and packed 30 + packets and brought it back by plane ( what an effort)

So its has to be good.

If you've been following my reviews you'll know that my comments are very Conservative and alway "under promised" & over performed, always way above what I shared and you'll not be disappointed.

Having Chinese New Year reunion dinners in restaurants are rarely pleasant experiences. This year's experience was no better, despite a recommendation that Famous Kitchen's food was supposed to be good.

We chose the $318 menu for 4, and had to top up an additional $79.50 because its on a per pax basis and we totalled 5. No sharing. Fair enough, I thought.

We were told to be seated by 4.45pm as dinner will start promptly at 5pm. It started around 5.10pm when all tables were filled. We felt like we were in a Chinese wedding banquet. The food streamed in unison.

Salmon yusheng was fine. No surprises there.

When they dished out the crabmeat fish maw soup, it came in a small pot which hardly filled 5 bowls. It could have filled 4 nicely. And mind you we paid for 5 pax.

Fish was OK. No surprises there too.

Broccoli was over cooked. Mushroom was  soaked way too long. Sea cucumber was acceptable. Portion seems to be for 4.

Noodles was for 3 pax. No garnishing. Plain appalling and forgetful.

Dessert was sugary water decorated with bits of fungus and chestnuts.

Service started out fine, courteous and prompt in the beginning but ended up rushed. We felt as though the restaurant had run out of plates as they were clearing them as fast as dishes were served.

Sorry for the long post. For almost $500, it was outrageous and for a first timer visiting this eatery, consider it my last. I'm surprised a renown brand will wager their reputation to stage reunion dinners like these. Shameful.

Malay braised noodles, or Mee Rebus is a comfort food since childhood growing up in Singapore's multicultural heartland. And tucked in the heartland of Singapore is this Muslim food stall of more than 4 decade's history moving from location to location over the years. On offering is a few basic dishes only, Satay from 230pm, Mee Soto and of course Mee Rebus their specialty. Menu starts from $3.50, $4.50 Power Mee Rebus or $6 Extra Special. In general, Mee Rebus is a yellow noodle dish, and most places offer them with bean sprouts, fried taukua, green chillies and hard boiled egg, topped with fried shallots. The star is always the thick, taucheo sweet potatoes sauce with rich umami. Different stalls uses different braising base from mutton, beef, chicken, dried shrimps, ikan bilis to even swimming crab as soup base of the sauce. Some has strong taucheo taste, some rich while some watery, and mostly too sweet. Hence at Rahim's their rich and thick sauce has the right consistency, not too starchy and not too sweet. Enough savoury umami to coat the sauce, ans unique to this stall, top with a coat of peanut satay sauce. And on the side, if you like it spicy, black chilli and ketchup manis to add depths to the flavour. Enough sauce to coat the chewy noodles nicely, and add a whole lime to give the broth a tangy twist. The Power version gets you tumeric flavoured boiled chicken slices, and the extra special gets you a whole chicken leg. The chicken is nicely marinated, juicy and simmered to the right texture. Enough to bite chunks off the chicken meat, flavourful and tender. Bean sprouts and vegs provide crunch to the dish, and my only gripe is missing fried shallots or would have made this 5/5.
Price reasonable lots of choice for u to dine alone or with family. Will patronise more if i happen to be around the area.

Expensive porridge that doesn't really justify it's price. Huge variety of porridge type though.

The three eggs porridge tastes very weird. Like the healthy soya bean and you tiao. But other than that, no diff from eating porridge at hawker.

I love Chester Express! Have been patronising this stall since it first opened years back as I live near the market. Love the mains in general - chicken chop/pork chop/sirloin steak/grilled fish/breaded fish etc and the side dishes (including pasta) are well proportioned too. Tasty and adequate portion sizes. Recommended!

Joining their membership is good deal, pay $68 and get 80 points in return which is equal to $80 (to be used in 12months), every meal gets 10% rebate , birthday month gets 20% rebate. üòÄ
Since unable to travel this time, here is the best place to indulge when miss üáØüáµ . Food was nice, staff was friendly and nice ambiance.

Had dinner there with family.
My 1st attempt on Japanese food. The taste was not bad at all. My other family members seemed to enjoy the food there.
The food served was fast.
The staffs were friendly. We were initiated to transfer to a more cosy corner for our family feast.
Indeed felt like in a Japanese restaurant atmosphere there due to the interior deco.
Good food! Good location, although place a little small but have friendly staff and price is also reasonable

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
They stand out for their tasty marinated pork. Go for both the marinated and garlic, won‚Äôt go wrong!

Only issue is the queue at dinner times and the smell that accompanies you after the meal.
Mutton Briyani tasted good and soft but should have more given (accounting for the chunk of bone that comes with it). The bigger piece I had was 95% bone and the smaller piece was all bone.

I really like the spacious feel of the restaurant.
Came during dinner time and the dim sum was all sold out. Other dishes we wanted to order was sold out.

Food here is generally alright, we liked everything except the trio platter. Just skip that as it was not very nice.

Dry laksa is nice and I like the wrap as it reminds me of peking duck and their dessert yam was served in a amazing view with dry ice and smoke pouring out

Was very very disappointed with the services of staff ‚ÄúSira‚Äù an Indian lady. She was very rude to me and have no manners and respect .  I complained to her manager but instead of apologising to me , she defended  her staff.  I can‚Äôt tolerate such behaviour.  My lunch was served with anger and it was so toxic to eat the laksa I ordered.  I did not enjoy my meal at all.  I went back to the manager to get the No of the owner but she just pointed to me to a number and ask me to go take that down.  I could not find any number.  I want to get in the Owner Jordan to explain in detail.  Can Jordan please message me here
Reasonably priced penang food. Tasty and value for money. But don‚Äôt expect anything fancy as it is meant for a regular meal.

Tried the briyani.
Nothing special, the mutton is really small.
Feel that the spice and fragrance is missing

Used to always patronized this place during yesteryears. Came back and it still e same. thou I miss the 'used to have' nasi lemak there but still the current food is still good, service and atmosphere still e same. I enjoyed!
Best taste and quality food

Really bad attitude from the wanton char siew stall server. A customer was in front of me, behind me there were tables and chairs...also have to keep a distance from the person in front...instead of asking me nicely, she gave me a blackened face and said:' why can't you stand here and pay here!'
I was still right in front of the stall and was only towards the right side.... I could not hear her when she asked for my order as she was preparing noodle and asking with her head faced down. There and then it started this bad attitude.
Perhaps the server might be feeling down that day but please never direct this to the customer. Food is mediocre and service attitude was so bad. Will not return again.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: Food is good, handmade! Better then the huge chain around Singapore with gold in the name. Staff is friendly too! Unfortunately I don't live near to eat it often.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Delicious.
no queue but forgot my food. checked with them and the guy cooking shouted at me. gangster behavior.
Ordered chicken rice the other day from this stall and it was subpar, portion was small and for $4 I expected to be a little bit more filled. Hence the rating
An old-timer cosy Japanese restaurant that have existed as far as my memories could take me. The daily set meals are good value-for-money and worth checking out.

You can customise your bowl here . Option of thick bee Hoon noodle,  flat noodles , glass noodles etc

Soup variety pork bone , spicy yunnan pickled cabbage  , tomato üçÖ and another pepper version .

I got the yunnan pickled cabbage , it‚Äôs tangy , sour and very appetising .

You get to select the ingredients you want to add such as vege , meats, fish ball etc

Giving 5 star due to the customer service crew, food will be 4 star.
Love their beef rendang and BBQ chicken..Their homemade chilli is super duper yums. definitely highly recommended! Must try!

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Happy fun loving two ladies in the morning not to mention plus points great food. I eat there literally everyday and the fun and smiles and happy morning two staffs makes it a pleasant start of the day. Good staffs who are sweating at 645am but always giving good vibes. Thank you
Stir fried Vegetables was tasty but the steam fish was cultivated grouper. Lemon juice was too sweet.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: View is nice, went on a weekday night with not many ppl. Food was quite ok. Charcoal tofu was quite special. Flaming chicken is quite nice too with a hint of rose flavour. Chicken came with a basket of prawn crackers but not sure if its free-flow as to embarrassing to ask. The menu was abit confusing though.. per serving is for one ppl or shared portion? Price wise is abit on the high side. Staffs r quite friendly.

B grade hygiene and cleanliness. Variety of vegetarian and vegan options available and freshly cooked Everyday unlike other Indian cuisine serving canteens at other halls. Tastes much better when compared to other Indian canteens too!
Closes by 8pm.

Went on 1st May.  Manager say chef is struggling to cook the food . Took approx every half hour to serve 1 dish at a time but the food came is cold and horrible. By the closing time cannot feel at least half full. Feel like been cheated. Blacklist big time.

Satisfying fresh take on the classic mee rebus dishes. A good authentic taste of mee rebus topped with a satay peanut sauce and if you prefer it with chicken and extra $1. Overall, a good plate of mee rebus but nothing special about other than the addition of satay peanut sauce. Service was fast and sometimes a short queue will be require during peak period.
P.S since its in Broadway kopitiam chain, expect the drinks to be super overpriced.

Food 3/5
Price 4/5
Dessert - /5
Ambience 2/5
Service 4/5
Slightly cheaper and less choice compared to other McDonald's restaurants in Singapore and, sadly, the only option for a late dinner in NTU.

I do not like to call others lazy or slow but their idle demeanor and inefficiency is unbearable and simply intolerable. i went to order 4 pratas and 2 teh tarik for take away during national day to celebrate this happy occasion but their service was terribly slow and non-chalant. Are your workers paid to  mill about taking their sweet time or are they here to operate an FnB business? If i am the boss of this establishment i would get rid of the whole lot of them and have them replaced,  it's like the staff just do not care about their work. This is the worst place to get my indian food fix.There are better quality service elsewhere such as across the road, I will not return to such a lousy place even if i was paid.

Usually order take-away but decided to dine in this time instead. Prata was excellent - freshly made and was perfectly crispy and chewy, one of the best I‚Äôve had! The briyani never disappoints. Rice was flavourful and meat was tender. Keep it up!

Dinner last Sunday 27th Oct: Thank you Xi Yan Maxwell for a most memorable dinner and evening!
Fine dining restaurants can sometimes be snotty and not usually so relaxed or comfy, but at Xi Yan Maxwell other than the excellent modern Chinese food to rival some of the best on offer in Singapore (crab beehoon 10/10), it was also very well priced for an unforgettable dinner in a very relaxed yet trendy setting. My birthday party group of 33 were made to feel very special with good attentive service that was not overwhelming - no pushiness to buy drinks, although I must say the wines are so completely affordable compared to the much higher prices you pay elsewhere for the same. We were a bit noisy but with our separated dining area, I am sure nobody noticed. When the cake was brought in I could hear guests outside the open door clapping - the restaurant arranged a very impressive one. It is this homeliness that I like about Xi Yan. Thanks once again for taking great care of us. We will be back again and again.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
Went there to try cuz always loves to eat fishhead noodles. It was quite normal only. Went for friend's birthday lunch, it was a small coffee or restaurant as it is called so table for 5 pax is possible. Foods are all very normal just like any neighborhood zichar. Had more better ones compared to this. Will only visit once. Staffs was friendly and very fun-loving with jokes. Bill was cheap tho - $60 for 4 pax

IG: mommyserene

My toman fish porridge set with added egg was ordered through GrabFood.

The congee is good. The thinly sliced ginger added nice contrast against the congee. However there was little toman fish slices in my bowl (4 slices to be exact). When I finally got to the bottom of the bowl, there was also the shocking absence of any egg.

Even after delivery, the oily stick chunks remained acceptably hard (not exactly crispy) instead of softening. The oily stick chunks were quite ok after soaking in congee.

Soy milk was as good as their congee. Pleasant tasting and at 30% sugar, not perceptibly sweet.

I probably would order again, but this time, avoid adding any additional items.

ordered a crabmeat fried rice.... didnt see any crab meat but tasted some chunks of meat that tasted like those kind of dried meat.. my friend ordered a tom tum fried rice, no taste of tomyum just taste like tomato fried rice :') price point was okay for that area (since it's novena) but $13+ for fried rice is not too good esp since didnt taste any crab ü•≤

Tender and well grilled meat! Overall, the meat is great but just wished that the portion is slightly bigger. The aglio olio was a miss though. Maybe can pick other sides instead. Will still come back to try other stuff!

Great ambience next to nature. Fantastic fresh air in the early morning and especially during the rain.
