Food is good quality with nice choice.  Occasionally staff not willing to serve, otherwise friendly.

Awesome Prata if you're in the yishun area. This is the original place of the huge branch down in Serangoon Gardens.

Great thosai too. But go for the Prata

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Shiok nasi padang...

Many dish choices available!

Everyday a special dish (like Briyani) is available.
Wonderful place to eat! The staff is very friendly amd the food is great

Went on boxing day Saturday evening just before 7pm and had to queue about 10 minutes.

Ordering is online via QR code and quite straight forward.

Waited for almost 20 minutes for our food which I think is a little long for ramen

I had the chicken based Ichikokudo Ramen (Extra Rich). Noodle texture was the best aspect of the ramen; stock was over salty and overpowered any chicken flavor. The chicken meat was not tender and stuck to the teeth. The egg was very ordinary.

My wife had the Hokkai Ramen Gifts from the Sea - Regular. The seafood was average at best. The stock way too salty even for someone like myself who likes salty food. At least the seafood stock wasn't too overpowered by the salt.

The iced green tea at $1.90 is a rip off. More like iced water with no green tea taste at all.

Overall 2 star rating for food and service staff.

Was surprised this place is quite crowded. Sitting area is limited & my sense is that they are not fully maximising their space, eg 2 person sitting 4 person seat. They can always spit the big table into 2 smaller tables. Food wise, it's normal thai food. Chicken wing & prawn cake were quite oily. Taste wise still ok. Basil chicken is tasty. For pad thai, the portion is very small. No gst nor svc charge. Ice water isnt served. This place is good for residents in the vicinity, personally i wouldnt travel for this.
The wait time between dishes during the dinner is an absolutely disappointing experience.
Cosy western food restaurant with great food. However some grilled cuisine requires chilli sauce or pepper to enhance the favour. The platter and apple pie is good. Overall not bad.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Probably one of the best fish bee hoon soup in Singapore, richer tasting soup and they give you a generous amount of fried fish
I like that place. Tomyum soup is absolutely yummy...
Nice authentic Thai food in Singapore. Enjoyable dinner with family
First time trying out the food. Like the food, its variety and service at this outlet.

Average food that's slightly pricier than surrounding Muslim food. But I like their coffee. Staff can get impatient during peak hours.

Busy but Generally can find seat during peak hours.
Great food and clean

Visited outlet around 4.30pm off peak period. We glad to have Sushi Go in Ang Mo Kio Hub cause previous only have one which is at Jurong Point. Even its not much customer but we found that two staff Vicky & Poh Lian providing good service. They keep attention on every customer. Always keep our table clean and tidy. Company should rewards their good service. üëçüèª  Keep going!
Your old school western food! We love it so much and will coem back here again... Hope to see more new menu in the future  üòÑüòÑüòÑ

(Translated by Google) Good Brian

(Original)
Good Briani

Dropby the Yishun outlet opposite Orchid Park Sec School, standard drop dramatically. Ordered Chicken Biryani but the photo i attached is what i got. Just 2 pieces of chicken, not even a breast or thigh. No papadum as well, where the photo clearly shows there is papadum. When asked, the lady rudely replied: "is just photo, not real" Do take note fellow customers when ordering. This is by far the worst Biryani I had so far.
Great place! I ordered the chongqing chicken. It is amazing and the amount of chicken is very generous. If you like spicy food this is your dish.

RUDE ATTITUDE, BEWARE!

I went alone for my lunch and wanted to eat Penang food, but upon reaching there. It was packed with lunch crowd, I decided to eat at the china food stall besides it, as there were seats available. After finished, I thought why not have a Cendol, I politely went over to this penang food shop and asked one of the aunties if I can order from them and eat at the shop beside. One of them who looked plump rudely brushed me aside by saying.. "Don't know, you go ask that china shop can eat or not" OK, I went back and asked for permission and they said ok, no problem. I went back to order the Penang Cendol and said I seated at next shop.

The aunties started to gossip among themselves and very grumpy, grouchy about it. I told them the shop already said ok, since you told me to ask them. One of them asked me to pay up first in a rudely tone.. OK, never mind. I paid up and went to my seat. A skinnier with short hair and slightly grey hair bespectacled auntie came over with the Cendol and rudely said to me..."Next time, you come take yourself." By the way, my table is just right next to their table.

Seriously! I paid up as per instructed and now i have to collect Cendol myself? and deserved your rude service? If can I eat at your shop, do you think i need to order from you and seat at other shop? You could have tell me not allowed in the first place and not showing me attitude.

Please use your brain and think.

The owner seriously need to train their staffs, since they are in the servicing line. If there is negative rating, I will give -100.

Bunch of cantankerous menopause aunties! NO MORE NEXT TIME!

Nice hot and spicy. Take mild and try. Add the egg as it helps to lower the spice. Dun try to be superman on your first try.

This shop do help to separate those items that can or should be tried. A different take
Spice level linger so try to go easy. Very solar to the ones I eaten in most part of china when I was oversea.
.

Overpriced and under delivered. I asked to take away a $6 soup and $6 chicken wings. The soup came in a small plastic container and it was only half full. And the 4 pc chicken wings was basically 2 wings and 2 drumsticks. If you‚Äôre are going to charge so much at least have the quantity to match. Or taste good. If I can get the same food from a coffee shop western shop, why would anyone come and eat here.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content:
Truly enjoyed the meal..ordered the ayam taliwang set. The main sambal is not overly sweet which i like..but the taliwang sambal was the best ..spicy and punch a kick. Asked for extra main sambal added with no extra cost..wanted to add the taliwang sambal too but felt so 'paiseh' to ask..lol. the grilled chicken was pretty decent , a good heathier alternatve to fried ones.
4 stars is because felt the rice could have been more grainier it was a little mush..but still nicely flavoured with a hint of lemongrass and coconut
Good South Indian fare at affordable prices. Quality maintained at all times and if you are having the rojak, don't forget to ask for more gravy! Relaxed, no frills dining experience.

This place has a home cooked feel about it. The staff are friendly and understanding but not overly stiff.

I ordered classic basic nasi lemak and chose my own sides.  I feel that it may have been more economical to just purchase one of their sets. The beef rendang was soft and the sauce was nice. What I do appreciate is that it had less salt in all of their food.  They make their own Chile which was not too spicy.

I take one star off because 1 plate of food plus 1 drink set me back $10. I won't be able to afford to eat here that regularly.
My neighbourhood best food place to go to. Superb tasty, and highly recommended. Authentic foodntaste

One of very few really good nasi padang stalls in ToaPayoh/Bishan/AMK area. Unfortunately, the beef rendang was not available (cook was on MC or smthng) so I had to settle for the chix rendang. It was tasty, the pachri nenas & sayur lodeh was also good, the sotong dish was good too. I wish they had sambal belacan but they only had sambal blado left (arnd 2pm) üòâ. By the time I wanted to take fotos, there was nothing left on my plate ü§£ü§£ü§£.
side note: I've cooked beef rendang a few times before & the spices my wife prepared made it ohh-so-delicious!... BUT... I was the one who had to c-o-n-t-i-n-u-o-u-s-l-y stir and turn the beef chunks in the wok for THREE WHOLE HOURS! For those who didn't know, this is why beef rendang costs 2-3x more than chix rendang (chix rendang requires about one hour only to stir and turn). üòÉ

They have a 2pax promo now where you get to choose 6 dishes + 2 bowls of rice + dessert. All for $39.90 before GST & tax. SUPER VALUE FOR MONEY.

Although, for a vegetarian restaurant, their one vegetable dish that we had (long bean) was not good. The long beans were quite old and too hard and fibrous when you bite into it. Please order another Vege to try!

Found their service to be prompt and good, probably improved since there were a few complaints about this from the reviews months ago.

Must order:
Butter Abalone Mushroom
Crispy soy nuggets
Truffle Hakka Abacus Seeds

Don't order:
Long bean with chai po
Decent Chinese restaurant hidden within AMK ITE. Good location for a family gathering. Food wise was normal, nothing much to rave about. Prices was affordable. Service was good.
Disappointed travel from Bukit Batok it just like most ZIchar so outstanding but ok
Nice

I placed my order via Deliveroo. I realized i had the wrong item order immediately after i pressed the sent button. I then immediately asked Deliveroo to help cancel my order via live chat. But the Deliveroo chat told me the order could not be canceled as the delivery was already on the way. How can the delivery be on the way 1-2 minutes after the order was sent in?

I tried to call the restaurant five times, but nobody answered the call. This will be the last time i order from this restaurant.

came here for dinner during weekdays.

maybe due to the sectional designed of the restaurant, it‚Äôs difficult to get attention and one ordered dish was missed out too.üòì

wanted to try the Signature Roast Duck but was ran out.  Mango Sago ran out too.üòÖ

the Crab & Fish Maw soup and the Fried Sesame ‚ÄúWuxi‚Äù Pork Ribs were good!üòã

the dark ambience and the decor are very unique.

There were only three people ahead of me but the queue moved very slowly. Out of 7 choices displayed, only 3 or4 were available. Food quality seemed to have dropped. Only the rice and chilly still taste good. Ikan bilis are very small and the fried chicken was tasteless although it still kept its crispiness. Overall, this is still an above average nasi lemak meal. Thanks to the fantastic chilly.
üëç

Variety: 5/10
Taste: 5/10
They only serve processed meat but DLLM has meat on sticks and satay sticks. The rest of the ingredients are pretty much the same. Taste wise,  the seasoning is not as flavorful as DLLM. But,  their homemade chilli sauce is really good.
Overall,  it was ok but I'd still prefer DLLM as they have real meat.
I like the modern twist of chinese food here . Xi Yan is added to my "I-shall-return" list.

I never dabao this before but I heard many whom takeaway dry will not get the soup. The soup is the best Penang laksa I tasted in SG. Better than Penang cause it‚Äôs more sweet and gao with chilli pack a punch.

Uncle very straightforward, just tell him your order. Take, pay money and enjoy my mee.

This eating place is hidden in the Any Mo Jio HDB estate, and it has both air-conditioned and alfresco sitting. The meat platter is nice, especially the prepared beef, which is tender and juicy. The starter platter on the other hand is just average. The restaurant is overall good value for the food served.

Ordered the basic tonkotsu

Broth, a bit light on the pork flavor, but compensated with strong mushroom fragrance. I suppose to get a deeper flavor without being too greasy.

Char siu, nothing special, thin. A bit bland, a bit tough

Noodles, pretty good, thin-style, semi-firm; not overcooked.

Price: very affordable. $6.90 for tonkotsu, but they have a $5.90 chicken soup version available
Food is not bad. But we waited very Long for the next dish to arrive. Like 20 minutes?

Awful experience! Buy at your own risk. No price menu available. Did not expect a packet of char siew and siew york rice to cost $6! Order 3 packets and add one egg each to 2 packets. Total cost $19.40. I politely ask for the breakdown, the server on my left very fiesty and unhappily provide the breakdown, $6 a packet, egg 0.70 cents each. After she took my order, she had the order written on a piece of paper and clipped with an olden days wood cloth clipper. She threw my paper order into a basket to display her unhappiness. I kept quiet waited for order to be ready and left. Seriously, many places out there serve fantastic roast meat and char siew. The food is overpriced, as it is a simple setup like a coffee shop, and the server attitude is unpleasant and rude. No STAR at all!
Friendly staff + Nice food = Happy Customer

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Great food and service at reasonable price. Will surely recommend the restaurant to extended family and friends

Definitely a worth a visit to Mookata Lor! The ingredients especially the meat were of good quality and really well seasoned. And can i say, the soup was amazing, its the first time that I did not add the maggi seasoning into the soup as the soup base on its own tasted so good I did not want to ruin it. Furthermore, everything is very affordable and I do seeing myself making frequent trips to my new mookata hideout!

Tucked in a quiet corner on the 2nd level next to Tanjong Pagar hawker center, it is many times "Out of sight, out of mind" in its location.
After reading many positive reviews, I ordered a deep fried fish with rice.
The soup was added with milk and a  generous amount of deep fried egg, seaweed, tomato and leafy greens. Soup was good though not outstanding. 5 pieces of deep fried fish nuggets which were still piping hot. More crusty and it had a larger batter than the fish slice. Couldn't tell much of the fish type.
Aircon seating filled quickly but the  service is quick and friendly as they will try to get you a table at the outdoor (large fans were observed).
For the price, it is reasonable.
Nice food but watch out, sometimes the fried chicken a bit raw inside.
Great value food, especially the 1 for 1 lunch.
Prata and thosai were alright. Bru coffee was a tad sweet but that was my fault for asking 100% sweetness

Finally managed to try it on my 3rd visit as they were closed when I tried to visit earlier.

Try sweet and sour pork as it was highly recommended in  the reviews. Love that they use lean meat and the taste is well balanced and does not feel oily. Although the portion is labelled as 'Small'  I think it is good enough to be shared between 3 to 4 pax.

Black bean noodles is great üëçit is chewy and taste authentic. Portion is HUGE. I think 1 bowl can feed 2 girls or 3 small kids.

Kimchi is great and they are refillable.

Their service crew was quick in noticing that we were having trouble trying to eat the noodles and offered us a pair of scissors to cut them.

Will definitely go back to try other dishes.
Great food as usual üòã

Our first time patronizing this stall and eating gado gado, bee hoon soto with extra packet of cracker to go with.
When we ran out of the peanut sauce, the stall owner saw, came over and offered to top up the peanut sauce to go with the remaining cracker.
Thank you so much! I'm sure this made his and our day!
Authentic and quality foods. The taste of almost every dish is so "surprisingly" good. Not a huge portion per dish, price is reasonable with such standard.  Small stall probably family biz.
Food is good, place is spacious but carpark is expensive if you just go there for dining. Parked there for 30mins and I paid $4..
Wanted a drink while waiting for my appointment. Order soy milk but no more. Waitress is nice, she give suggestions recommending ÂÖ´ÂÆùËå∂which is not in the menu. Taste great.
Their dum briyani is really good dum briyani üëåüèΩ
Affordable zichar located at amk industrial. Wide variety of food choices and can BYOB foc. Food is tasty but some are abit salty for me.

Having patronized their Springleaf branch for more than a decade and half, it saddens me to admit that their quality has slipped. It's not unexpected, given their expansion in recent years.

Today was an example of their lost standards. I ordered their regular teh tarik, as a takeaway. It was filled up just over a quarter of the packet and the quality was just not there.

It's a shame seeing the sham that has become of this brand. I had good years with friends and family at their Springleaf branch, but I can't say the same now.

It‚Äôs just a counter for taking away, no seating for dining at the moment
It‚Äôs soft launching, has not officially opened yet. Thus no long queue, waiting time (after order placed) is about 5-10min, kitchen will prepare upon order (steam or deep fried)

Food wise, not everything on menu is available now, e.g char siew polo pau.

Price wise is at the high side. But taste was ok . Will patronage again
Good quality customisable pasta, although its on the pricier side. Very good and friendly service too.

Room for improvement but a good first visit nonetheless. Found Tanoke on restaurant week's list and booked to try but ended going ala carte instead. Nestled in small cosy space on the second floor of a shoplot building at Purvis St. Chic modern interior accentuated with the play of light. Quite a few favourites but after having 9 dishes off the menu, I found some of the elements used to be repetitive. Would love to see more variation in flavour and style.

We started of with the otoro aburi handroll and they were accomodating to cook one of the fish more and shift some of the toppings over to mine so I had 2 portions of uni and ikura(in pictures). We loved the wagyu marmalade toast and made a second order if it. The sweet buttery finish on the crisp toast and rich umami mash of braised wagyu complimented perfectly with the dollop of yuzukosho cream.

Refreshing, sweet tomatoes and tart vinaigrette a top creamy thick mascarpone tofu. Love! It's like a fusion take on italian tomatoes and burrata. Definitely order this. 3-cut wagyu platter failed to make an impression. These had a beautiful smokey aroma when served. A5 Kyushu tenderloin, A5 Kagoshima ribeye and MB7 Australian striplion. Meats were cut too thin, 1-1.5cm thick. Tenderloin had the best mouth feel and melts but was cooked done, no pink probably as it was cut the thinnest. The Ribeye section we got was bottom half fat and some pieces with gristle. Striploin is forgettable.

Even grilling on the US jumbo asparagus. Bonito flakes and yuzukosho cream made all the difference for this simple dish. Koji aged NZ coastal baby lamb, semi-frenched. Appreciated the clean cut, less fat and well seasoned outer char. Tender and juicy without any gamey scent. Great if you aren't a fan of fatty cuts. One day air dried flying squid was overkilled in chili flakes and meat itself was rather flat. I wouldn't recommend this. Iberico pork jowl with sweet karashi mayo. Decent but again overkilled in chili flakes. The mayo helped here. Love that it was served with pickled radish slices on the side.

Nice jiggly matcha pannacotta with strawberry jam and pistachio nuts to finish off the meal. The  Smores Tartlet would have been perfect if not for the marshmallows being extremely chewy. I shared that perhaps the marshmallows were not toasted long enough to caramelize and melt inside, or the ice cream on top made them harden back too fast. The tart shell was perfect, thin and cracked easily while holding firm. Lots of melty dark chocolate at the base and bits of raspberry inside that brought it all together. This was waved off the bill after my feedback and the kitchen agreed that this could be improved.

Naren took great care of us during our visit. I was offered a complimentary sake to try and was served the Senkin Modern Moku Junmai Ginjo.

A refreshing addition to the City Square Mall food options.

Wanton Mee: noodle is springy. Sauce was good. Wanton is so so. Soup is bland.

Curry Mee: Soup gravy is good. Noodle is nice. But overall, lacks the punch.

Overall: Recommended to go and try.

Affordable yakiniku place, however for big eaters may not be the best price(Big eaters may have to go for large rice[Upsize is free] and more meat). Meat is ok, ordered the Like set which has harami, short plate and tongue and ordered extra pork jowl. Best meats were the harami and pork jowl. The grill can be set to high or low temp, which is good for giving meats like harami a nice sear but not cooking it entirely to keep the inside juicy. However given that you are only given 50 mins i think most people will just set it at the highest temp. The grill is quite small, recommend going solo cause even if you go as a group you are still using the same sized grill, so 50 mins may not be enough. And because of the 50 mins time limit maybe hence why the meats are cut thin for quick cooking time. Same concept to ramen shops in Japan, you're going in for a fast meal not a social gathering. I would go again solo but if i we were to gather with friends i would go other yakiniku places.

Had been dining quite frequently at Dian Xiao Er branches, and the standard has been consistent. Besides their tasty signature roast duck, their pan fried cod and petai prawns are good too. üòã The dishes can be somewhat filling, so you have to know the portions they are serving before you get a good idea how much to order. Would recommend this place if you want to eat Chinese cuisine.

I was visiting NTU and stumbled on this salad bar. Everything was very fresh and yummy. Love it! Please consider opening an outlet in Jem, many ppl will patronise for sure and view salad in a diff light ü§£ one of the best and v affordable salads I‚Äôve tasted in a while! Just wish it was in a more accessible location ‚ù§Ô∏è

I ordered the ‚Äò100-Second‚Äô Stewed Yellow Croaker on promotion for $8. The soup although little, is extremely sweet from the fresh fish. The fish is very soft and smooth with great texture but many bones. Not for those who are fearful of fish bones.

As indicated on their website, "This signature PUTIEN dish is carefully boiled to precision at 100 seconds. It allows one to taste the true freshness of the yellow croaker. The original taste of the fish is accentuated, with the dish‚Äôs light seasoning of using onions, ginger, Fujian aged wine and Puning bean sauce. The perfect pairing of the tender fish with the sweet broth is best enjoyed piping hot upon serving."

I also ordered another 2 seasonal dishes, Spicy Fried Duotou Clams (UP $26.80), "Tossed over high fire, with just a touch of spice. A must-try!" and Putian Farmhouse Clam Soup (UP $28.80), "A traditional farmhouse recipe. Taste the delicate freshness of the clams in the soothing smooth soup." Both dishes when ordered together is $43.80

Both dishes are nice. The soup is not too salty and I packed half the portion since I can't finish it alone even without rice. The Spicy Fried Duotou Clams is actually a stir fried dish. I decided to remove all shells before eating with the sweet garlic snd spring onions. To me, it isn't spicy at all, tasted just like a little light sprinkling of pepper.

The chrysanthemum tea ($3.80) is non-sweeten and refillable. I like it that they don't add sugar to it.

Overall, I had a quiet lunch as I went in before noon. The staff were polite and able to advise me on my selection how the clam should be cooked as they have 9 ways of preparing it.

The food tasted good without making me very thirsty afterwards. Be prepared to pay a little more for better quality food. I paid $65.45 for my lunch today. The portion is sufficient for 2 pax with rice.

A nice restaurant around Toa Payoh. They serve Nepalese cuisine and western dish. Overall the food was okay, nothing fantastic but I gave 4 stars because the service was good and they are senior-friendly with a lot of discount.
Really tasty, superb
Just order a plate of rice with one chicken and one vegetable cost $6. Most expensive nasi padang rice in toa payoh

Fun concept with robots serving the food. We waited an hour for our food even though we entered the store at its opening hours. The experience seems consistent as the customers who entered at the same time with us were all waiting as well. New store opened with lots of teething things to sort out in its operations.

ÂíñÂï°ÊéíÈ™® is yummy, other dishes i had all tasty.
You better book the shop in advance.

The Penang char kway teow has wok hei and really good . The staff here has attitude , the management has to step up on training .

Penang prawn mee broth is nice but ingredients seems dry and shrunk in size attributed to repeated cooking .

Would u pay close to $50 for pekin duck skins ONLY? The meat is not inclusive, need another add-on of another dish in price range of another $10-$28) to get the meat dish. That was what was explained by staff/manager as stated in the menu. Usually, one would paid for the entire duck and another token sum for the meat to be cooked separately - which is acceptable. In any case, the Peking duck taste and presentation is below average (see pic). Would have given a 1-star if not for other dishes which tasted better and more value-for-money. Think there are better options and rational restaurants out there.
Good service and traditional feel and taste! Old traditional restaurants are always more tasty compared to those new modern types. Had a good birthday celebration for my dad. Highly recommended
Very nice wohei taste of the omelette. Blew me away! Very authentic thai taste and thai ambience! Will visit again
Chicken hotpot is nice..frog is also tender..BBQ meat skewers taste great too.. Price is neither cheap nor expensive.. atmosphere is good for some gatherings...

Prata wala is a convenient food joint located in Jurong Point especially as it‚Äôs opened during late hours. They make good variety of pratas and nans with really good chickpeas and butter chicken for gravy. Set meals are a good option for all-in orders. I‚Äôve been eating here for 6+ years. The place is usually busy even at night so waiting might be necessary. Ice Limau and masala tea is also good, with Bru filter coffee as a new edition. It makes for a good eat-in option but most good options finish post 7pm.

The staff is really working hard w.r.t. serving customers and online orders but they still manage to be available and have good service. Yesterday, We weren‚Äôt happy about not getting potato since it was almost over but they freshly made n even tried to give more than what we ordered. Such an example of service is worth mentioning.

Friendly service. First time dining in a Nepalese restaurant.

The fish and chips was a huge serving. The Nepali pork belly was extremely tender and flavourful, comes with pulau rice and Nepali salad.

We had the moumou for the first time. Nice sized and tasty. Are they suppose to taste like xiaolongbao with curry seasoning? :) Will find another moumou to compare.

I seldom post 5 stars, but this simply blows away.
We ordered fish and chips, lamb shank and mushroom soup.
Really good. Lamb shank meat easily slide off the bone, no weird gamey smell. The black pepper sauce complements well.
Mushroom soup flavory with real mushroom bits and spice.
Fish and chip also very good.
Paying slightly more than usual coffeeshop price but u get a high quality western food.
First time there to try their butter curry chicken. It was good. Will definitely go there again.
Nice pot of sukiyaki, beef. Sparkling peach from Japan, abit sweet. Enjoy the wonderful ceiling jazz strings music. Was the one customer to go at 940pm.
Currently there promotion ongoing for member. Expect to be crown during weekend dinner
BBQ platter & XO carrot cake standard seems to drop. Overall satisfactory.

Crocoach under table. Server aware of this and just shaking her head and say...ewww...

Food quality is declining
Western Food At Economical Pricing. Worth every penny. Better cook than their WWP branch
Nice, tasty and fast

Service is excellent and the food is great! Went twice since the outlet opened at AMK Hub! The Karubi set is worth the money! For normal adults, do opt for the 200g variant as 100g is definitely not enough to satisfy your cravings!

Do also come early to avoid the extremely long waiting time, which may take up to 2 hours during peak hours. For those who can‚Äôt afford to wait, you can always go for their takeaway menu bento meals which features the exact same items and the meat is properly cooked for you!

The rice noodle set is presented nicely, but taste was ok only, nothing extraordinary. Price is expensive if there is no 1-for-1 promo. Sour and spicy noodle is much better and half the price of the rice noodle set.
Some selling roti prata,didnt put the notice of foods price,every Roti prata shop the price is different.
They used to have very good broth of pork ribs, even the original-flavoured mixian was tasty. But now, the original broth just gives a taste of salt.
Okay lah ur maki is 2.80 but can charge more idm, just don't embarrass the Japanese people any further by making a maki like this. One Makis worth of tuna u split into 6 Makis.
Variety of Indian food during lunch hours.Reasonable and affordable price.Taste wise just ok..ok..and spicy.
Great western gourmet food in a industrial estate food court. Close to restaurant quality but at food court price.

I hate coming to this mamak. Very very slow service. Need to remind them once or twice to get your food ready especially their Thai food. Cooking wise, okay la so-so. They have new rojak corner, same thing.... I've order, told the kakak I'm coming back in 10mins, she acknowledged so i went. Came back and she asked if i have ordered....

I had fried basil seafood rice with egg. Not authentic but good enough for a quick lunch fix.
Flavour is not authentic but decent.
Good portion
The food and service is top tier, nice environment,and affordable as well. 10/10 would recommend üòä

The highlight of my visit to ‚Äúmalaysia chiak‚Äù is always the char kway teow.

Sprinkled with bean sprouts it was a delight and my greed would show whenever  I left my plate completely clean.

But not this time.

It has turned soggy and I left half uneaten.

I won‚Äôt be returning unless standards improve.

A plate is now $5 up from $4:50.
Quality has dropped. Ordered a Mega San but salmon sashimi as thin as a crabstick slice. Feedbacked to the contact us email but lacked response

Have been here a few times and was never disappointed with the food. Ordered Wagyu Stamina Don with Foie Gras, Chicken Nanban Don & 3 Kinds Sashimi this time. The dons were pretty good, but honestly the sashimi was the best! Each slice was fresh and thick, which is really worth it for $12.80 :-)

Authentic Thai eatery hidden along a stretch of shops. I did not realize it was a Thai eatery until recently I chanced upon it on Google and went to find it. I ate there with my colleague and we find it good and authentic. The portion is quite decent also.
I came back in the evening to take away pad Thai, pineapple fried rice and fried garlic pork for dinner. Generous portions and tasty. Slightly disappointed with the fried pork as it was soggy - might have been due to the take away journey.

Overall recommended and I will come back to try other dishes

Was there with my family on a busy night around 9pm. All of us agree that service was fantastic! Thank you assistant manager Fernando and team üòÉ

1. Even before we were shown our seats, the lady service staff pre-empted that orders might take longer due to shortage of manpower. We didn't wait more than 10 min after our orders. That's more efficient than I mentally prepared for

2. E-menu showed certain bundled items as unavailable, but they were mostly available separately. Fernando patiently helped to take the orders and proceeded to serve our food. (Disclaimer: We took quite a long while to decide)

3. Service staff was able to acknowledge our request for help with a simple hand gesture while continuing to serve another table, instead of simply ignoring us.

4. We stayed till closing and all the staff were cordial throughout without "black faces" or veiled sarcastic comments.

Kudos to the team!

Sidenote: One improvement that can be made is to the e-menu.
Root beer float was marked unavailable, but root beer and coke float were both available.
Value set was marked as sold out even though it is available on public holidays, but the soup and drinks were available separately.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
I generally liked the food here. The appetizer plate was well executed and they were still hot when served.

The Compoy with braised vegetables and steamed threadfin also left a lasting impression. Really liked the umami from the Compoy dish since most of the ingredients were naturally high in umami.

I think one very strong area for improvement is their service and attention to customers, which is the reason why I didn't rate them 5 stars. When ordering, we informed that one of our dining party was still on the way and requested for the food to be served later. 5 mins before she reached, we informed one of the staff to serve the dishes, but half an hour later, nothing was served. When we checked in with another staff, he had the cheek to tell me that we had requested for the food to be on hold even though our party had been there for a good half hour.

We also placed an order for the threadfin subsequently. However, 40 mins later, this was still not served and we had to check with the staff on the status. Because of these delays, we had to spend close to an additional hour at the restaurant. The service aspect really has room for improvement and to caveat, I'm not expecting service standards at a Michelin star restaurant.

Absolutely ridiculous how for a second time they fed me with spoiled food when i finally decided to come back months after they fed me spoiled spaghetti. How can you not smell the foul smell of your corn when they‚Äôre spoiled??? 0 food quality check in this store
To enter the restaurant you first have to pass by all the smoking customers in front of the door
Family run restaurant. Plenty of regulars who return time and time again.. Luv the Garoupaaaa Fish soup la... Niceee
Teochew porridge is cheap and yummy
One of the favourite western food stall. Fried fish Aglio Olio pasta tasted good. The fish is soft. Chicken steak, fries and mash potato also nice.

Service is amazing ‚Äî it is top notch. They even asked for feedback on the food and shared with me bad feedback from other customers when I offered them good feedback about the luffa.

The luffa and the fried tenggiri fish (with its accompanying sauce) blew my mind. The luffa was soft and absorbed the delicious superior stock very well. I never knew vegetables could taste so good.

Their in house chilli had depth in taste and was refreshing to pair with any dish.

I absolutely enjoyed my experience there.

Quite satisfied with the huge piece of chicken cutlet.  Nicely cooked.  I was the last customer at 8.30pm today.  Several others were turned away as the food was sold out way before the closing hours.  Queued for about 15 mins.  Waiting time for food was about 10mins.

#rasasayangwesternfood
Very good food.
Exceptional chirashi. I thought it was a bit pricier when i first looked at the menu. However when the food arrived, i thought the quality and portion justify the price!
Very good fried fish hoagie which is uncommon to find in Singapore. Personally like it better than the typical sandwich franchise offerings. Good pricing and casual ambience for family meals.

Seems like this is the only visible cafe around the corner surrounded by all the landed houses. My mom in law commented that this casuarina curry location is good because of the landed houses. I replied yeah but also due to the exit point of the awesome lower pierce reservoir trail. My mil and wife loved it although it seems to be a short trail maybe 1+ km only.

Anyway paper thosai is ok, ottapam (relive my memory when young treated by rajesh friend). Ginger tea are awesome after a cooling morning breeze walk!

This is probably the best Char Siew Ramen I have ever tasted, not your normal circular-shaped Char Siew that is cooked in soup.
The Char Siew is tastefully grilled with the right balance of lean and fat meat, making it juicy and succulent.

Have to agree with the other reviewers that the standard here has dropped, and prices are also too high.

Butter chicken and ultimate murtabak (filling is mostly mushroom btw) were not bad. They also forgot to serve my egg onion prata and I lowkey had to argue with them for it HAHA but I did get it in the end la
As we seldom eat beef, decided to try their fish, chicken and pasta. All were nicely cooked and seasoned, including the side dishes. Recommended!

Food and ambiance was great!
Crayfish was fresh

Looks authentically Thai but the truth is in the pudding. Mixed reaction for me. While the taste is overall pretty OK but the authenticity for 2 of the dishes - otah n grilled pork seems a bit lacking. Still I liked the grilled fish n tarmarin soup. 3.5 star for now. Will revisit in future and try the other dishes.
Pasta tastes pretty good, great service by Samir. Highly recommend! :)

Service was good. Crackers served as appetizer / snack came with chili sauce was perfect match, tasted good. The main dishes like pad Thai, belacan fried rice and clear seafood tomyam was also served within short time, tasted good too.
A great fast food option on campus. However some items are not available and there is no discounted price for students.

Almost ate a piece of hard sharp plastic found in the soup. When I complained, the staff said, "What? So you want a refund?" Shocking. Your only job is to open the plastic box that the soup was shipped in and pour it into the reheating device. Is it that hard to open a plastic box without plastic shards dropping into the soup?
A very different chicken broth ramen at this halal ramen restaurant. Thought the flavour is rich, it is distinctly different in taste compared to your typical ramen.
The French fries here are too dry and not crispy at all. But it's the only option students have here for for late night food.

Delicious food! I always get the butter chicken and naan here. They used to take your order at the table but now it seems like everyone orders their food at the counter. The food has always been a similar standard since I first started coming here. Spent quite a lot this time.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Lots of food options. Popular for carrot cake, hokkien mee and soya bean drinks. They have new store like chee Cheong fan and Korea food.
Relocatee. Friendly service. Delicious food. Price a bit steep but mostly worth it. Great for eating with family or sharing.

Great food at very reasonable prices.
The French Bean is very crunchy.
Has Asia and Western menu and plays contemporary background music. Great join to relax.
Found this place in a corner when I was looking around trying to get a quick bite. Service was fast and tasted better than I expected. Price was also reasonable. Will come again for sure.
There was quite a queue to eat there but didn't have to wait long as the service was fast. Didn't have to wait long for the food either. Food was delicious.

Chui Xiang has much to offer.
Food without MSG.
Selected decent pricing dishes (eg whole soon hock fish around $20, white pepper Sri Lanka crab less than $50).
And most importantly, great cooking!
This is one of the restaurants among Casuarina road that operates for a long time, I attributes it's long standing towards the value and quality of their food.

Quite a quiet place despite the loud lights and decor - the food was nice and reasonably priced. Had the sour spicy soup which was suitable for 3-5 pax. However it was so good that i finished it eventhough it was only 2 of us. The skewers were well seasoned and i enjoyed the chicken innards skewer although we were deceived by the sausage skewer thinking it was the taiwanese sausage but it turned out to be just overpriced ntuc sausage. The barley was another plus point. Not too sweet and was cooling after a hot meal. Overall, would return for a meal again and to try other dishes.

Lovely fluffy rice, fish curry lacked kick...veg was ok. Masala tea a mite sweet.Restaurant ambience comfortable. 45 mins stated for 'eating time'but be mindful you may not have your meal served for 10 mins. Staff look like they mean business...Not a bad lunch but for SGD 13......Halal of course...

Delicious meals are tasty especially the Pan fried bun & Shanghai soup bun really suprised me its so yummyüòã
Food serve quite fast n service was good tooüëçüèª
definately will come back here again.
Best hainanese white chicken. Fuss free and so singaporean. Good mix of other local doses as well
Bad service and lousy order pickup management. The cashier was rude and the aunties are so blur, not helpful in checking order.
Affordable and good quality Japanese food.  I like the service where they provide free flow of hot tea.
Excellent and authentic

Lousy food standard quality ...inconsistent ... ordered egg prata but turned out plain prata with some bit of egg at corner. Was told its like that bcos its busy period. Is that how they serve? ...can't do proper prata during peak period ??? Also most part of prata was so tought that can't be eaten!!! Lousy service, & bad attitude !!!
Superb service n on dot typical Indian food at Jurong area. Thanks bro.

Serves a great variety of Asia food & snacks such Penang char kway teow, claypot chicken rice, Mee Rebus, Mee Siam, Nasi Lemak, popiah (turnips wrapped in a roll). Highly recommend claypot chicken rice for first timer.
One of my family's favourite restaurants. We always enjoy the food here!
Good sushi expirence.
Excellent reasonably priced Thai cuisine. We love the lemon grass steam fish.
Nothing special for the hike up price for the food.

Ordered the ribeye with garlic merlot sauce (200g) and I must say it‚Äôs totally worth the price at $18.90.
The ribeye I have at other places usually serves with the bone intact but here the chef took away the bones and made it so much easier to eat. Ordered medium done to perfection. As the sauce blends well with the meat too, every mouth is full of flavours. Portion is big too and one feels really full after the meal. Curly fries are nicely done and very crispy.

Highly recommended üëçüèª
Disgusting food. Ordered Nasi goreng kampong . Received white rice. No salt no spices at all. Expensive

I usually like my food cooked well, hence #Sashimi is just not my kind of food. Plus i am very sensitive to fishy smell, the slightest smell will just explode in my nose when the fish is not fresh. But... I'm about to change that. #ConfidenceRegained
.
First time having a #ChirashiDon, i must say i am pleasantly surprised, especially when paired with #GrilledUnagu. Even ate a few slices of #Salmon, #SwordFish, #YellowTail and #Tuna (no mercury-like taste üëçüèªüëçüèª).
.
Loved their #DeepFriedOctopus, goes well with #Mayonnaise (available upon request). The #BbqEggRolls are pretty tasty too.
.
So glad that we have a decent #JapaneseRestaurant here in the #West, #TamanJurong. #Kotobuki is a great gem serving great #JapanseCuisine.
.
#StanRecommends #StanzFoodHunts @kotobukisg #KotobukiSG #Jurong

Bought fried rice for $10 and say I chose this.
Food: 5/10
Service: 3/10

We are surprised to receive 1 slice of birthday cake as Jack heard that we have birthday girl when he served us ice cream.

Salmon sashimi is fresh, chicken curry don has large portion and sesame ice cream not so sweet.

Good service  and attentive to customer needs.

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: Very affordable and decent mookata. I am happy they have a few sets for us to choose. One set is enough for 4 to 5 pax.

Bad experience and service, the two of us eating gave us a table for two but really small, we wanted to order a lot of food so asked for a bigger table as there wasn't enough space for our food, but they would rather let us seated at individual tables side by side instead of a table of 4 with lots of empty tables for 4 as we were not formally dressed nor Singaporean and couldn't seem to afford it. Many other 2 people who ordered less than us (only 1 set meal to share) got a table for 4 and ate comfortably. The food was so so, but Hotate Mentai Yaki disappointed me as the pictures and the food really didn't match. Really not worth eating, will never come again.
Best of west
jus aany other macdonald but note that they dont allow the mcdonald app deals

Extremely generous portions and the staff who attended to me, Vijay, was very helpful. He took my order over the phone and when I arrived to pick up, everything was packed and ready! I ordered the Mutton, Ikan Bilis and Prawn Satti Soru. The leftovers tasted great the next day too. Raita and Papadum was included in the meal, making it very authentic. Love!
The name is 'Lok Lok' which diners dip food skewered with sticks in melting pot to cook, the variety can be better. But price and dessert variety is alright.
The outlet provides average fare at reasonable prices.

Been to this outlet many times.es probably once a week for dinner at about 8 plus. Never ever disappointed with the food especially the xiao long pau. I always  lazy to scan the QR code to place oder a d was always assisted by Su Fei in ordering.  She always serves with  a smile.  Keep it up!!

Lok lok that is more hygienic than the ones you find in Malaysia cause you get a brand new pot of lok lok base to dip your food into.

Decent selection and a good place to go if you're craving for lok lok. They charge by a bundle of 100 pieces or you can go for the buffet option where you get free flow of drinks and ice cream too.

V awesome dining experience. Staffs were attentive and food were served fast. We had an enjoyable dinner. I like the soup alot. The restaurant even served free kid meal. cabbage mushroom rice with daopok as sides. Yam with duck was excellent too.
Food was not too bad.  Thought fried garlic topped on spaghetti was a bit overwhelming for me,  bitter taste.  For S$7.90, I guess the portion is slight small for most.
Waited for quite after I was sitted before someone attended to me for my order and the seats are not comfortable...a bit stuffy and warm.

Inform staff to check with kitchen several times but did not bother to get back to us. Saw the opposite table who came in way later than us already got their food and we are still waiting. In summary, bad and slow service. Not recommended to go during peak lunch hours if you cannot wait at least 45mins for your food.

Excellent service in introducing food and meeting specific dietary requirements by Ms Zhang Lan.

Food is nice.
Special mention on lor mee, starters, chilli and tea...
Great food. But service is slow.

It is my first time trying Buddha jump over the wall. You need at least 10 ppls and need to preorder in advance. Their other food dishes also not bad. In total, the cost for each person is about $100..

Service is impeccable. The cooking style for the food is interesting but IMO, no wow factor. Yu sheng is too fusion to my liking and having rocket leaves left a bitter taste to the yu sheng - not very appropriate considering this is supposed to be an auspicious dish? Can't say much about the white bee hoon as well - it is tasty but no wow factor. The grilled pork combi with the pineapple is refreshing though.

Did a double take when I walked past this shop coz of the super garden decor hanging from the walls and ceiling! Ordered some items to share and here's what I think:

1)Tom Yum soup is super spicy!!! Not for the faint hearted. Tastes great, but next time I will ask them not to put the cut chili padi inside.

2) Olive fried rice was salty (as it should be) but fried until fragrant too. Nice touch to add the thinly sliced mango.

3) Red Ruby with jackfruit to cool down my mouth after the Tom Yum fire.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Quite a nice Nasi Lemak. Rice not as fragrance though. Overall quite good and expect some queue.
Good handmade fishball with Malaysian style black noodles. The fishballs are good. Not like the standard factory produced like many other places. There's a queue most of the time.
Overstocked salt from Covid ah? Pan fried far cry compared to Ding Tai Le

First time coming to this cafe and will definitely go back again. It‚Äôs such a nice and comfortable place to chill in..The food is nice & My family simply love all the varieties that we have ordered.. üëçüèª

Location: Pet friendly cafe located near a vet, a small park, catsmart, petlovers, and a nearby cafe to chill with your pooches after having a walk at lower pierce reservoir, ample parking.

Cafe: Came here a few times. Cafe is very spacious for small and big groups but price wise is a bit on the high side. I find a cup of cappuccino at $7 quite exp. Got the caramelized (coffee with a whip of caramel at $8). Food is acceptable & bug portion but not so fantastic. Service is very good, staff will immediately ask a choice of cold or warm water, and provide a water for the pooch too. We'll come back for small bites and some drinks.

Not the best Japanese restaurant and guess this is what I can expect in Jurong Point. Price range is normal and tasted ok. First time I tried set meal and this time around I ordered ala carte. Service was good and less crowd. They sell sushi and sashimi at the entrance if you opt for a takeaway. Hotate sashimi was not bad but slightly thin. Total bill $40.37 for one pax.

Good quality ramen at affordable prices! The tonkotsu broth is thick and super flavourful with melted pork bits floating around, showing it‚Äôs the real deal slow cooked. Noodles done just right which are qq, portion more than generous. Once in awhile the charsiu may be on the drier side, but still tender to the bite, beating many ramen ‚Äúrestaurants‚Äù. Chicken clear broth gives you one big fat drumstick and thigh with a flavourful yet light soup base and generous noodle serving.

Did I mention the price? $7 for the charsiu tonkotsu and $6 for the clear chicken broth, it‚Äôs super worth it! This place will always have my support for an alternative for ramen Keisuke tonkotsu king which I feel tastes very similar and really good
Reasonable price and good food. I used to come here for lunch and nice place to get together.

The roast meat are nice, but the owner and staff attitudes are horrendous and overly greed driven.

If you dine in, be prepared that before you finish eating, they start to clear your plates to chase you again. They can do that because they already made you paid upfront, whether you finished your food or not, it‚Äôs none of their business anymore.

The owner is too egoistic that customers will patronise them no matter how bad their service are.

A lot of up selling when you place order, their pricing is not cheap to begin with.

Recent bad experience was they imposed ( no signage or notice , just simply refused your order if you want to share the portion ) a minimum order ( of one person set ) per person when this is a hawker food stall !

Avoid if you can, there are better food around.
Super value for money western food!! Food service is friendly and prompt!

I have visited Ichiban Boshi in Jurong point outlet on 22/7/2022 at night. I have been served by uncle Charles who are very patient and provide exceptional service to us. Uncle Charles provided prompt service when we needed. He also offered to help us take picture. Other than that, he are attentive to our needs and pour for us tea when we finished it. I really enjoyed his service. His service make my day and I have recommend my friends and family to Ichiban Jurong Point to eat.

I hope that you can award him with awards or give him recognition as he leave me a good impression about Ichiban Boshi. His service impacted me greatly and I will visit Jurong Point outlet again.

We ordered FuRong Omelette, MaPo ToFu, baby kailan, hot & spicy boneless chicken. The food was delectable! The service was outstanding. Short-staffed but still attentive. They checked if we preferred chopsticks or fork/spoon. They made sure we knew size portion, etc. They communicated well. Everything arrived quickly. Beer was served ice-cold as well. Premises was spotless and tables very clean. No GST and no service charge, so definitely deserve a tip!
Good tastes for original Beijing flavour cuisine. Spent S$200+ for 4 people. Xiao Long bao and guoti are also good.
Good food in my neighborhood. But, the server working there is dismally unhappy.

Review from a westerner: This a great little shop! Burger is the best you'll find in a coffee shop and very affordable for the quality. Haven't had a bad meal with these guys and our kids love it too. :)
Not bad! I tried their setC which is rendang beef set. Recommended. It come with blue colored nasi lemak!

Nice food, reasonable price.

Super love their food, my kids love it too. Kids eat prata, eat in, the prata is super crispy.
Very good place to enjoy mala on a rainy day with a fried twist to the usual potatoes

No number to show that the food order is ready, no one wraps your food in a paper bag, no wasabi, soy sauce provided.  I have to asked a customer service to help me,He said that the chef in the kitchen was preparing, and let me wait there for nothing. and then I would ask the customer service to provide it. Poor service.
Delicious fish soup!

Super Thai is indeed a hidden gem. It was my first visit and was impressed with what they got to offer. Food and drinks prices were reasonable and I will certainly be back! The staffs and crew were entirely Thai; dining there is as if you were in Thailand! Warm friendly and meticulous. Will certainty not be my first!

Terrible service. I ordered a seafood aglio olio‚Ä¶  waited for an hour. I got all different food except my pasta‚Ä¶ üôÑ. Their alcohol was the only this worth it here. Other then then there is no point. Do NOT order the food here.

Opens till 11pm. A viable substitute for the Whampoa food centre if it‚Äôs closed for cleaning or for the day. Beef hor fun had some wok hei. But spinach isn‚Äôt a good substitute for Cai Xin. Wrong texture.

Service by Mr.Nareenth & Iris are fantastic and Awesome!
The food here is delicious! Definitely be back.
Have new year set here. In general satisfied with  food and service. A bit crowded but still acceptable for the team gathering.
Staff very friendly to kids. Food is serve quite fast. Very windy. However if you want to order takeaway or drink at the counter, staff does not even attend to you until you stand in front of them.
Portion was generous and decent for the price, pretty high standard for Coffeeshop Western food. Will come back again
Delicious food, nice servers
Should patronise this eatery if you are near that area after a walk at lower pierce reservoir.
Taste not bad.Love the small fish most.Although is small,but not over fry.Many stall over fry small fish,taste not good. ÊòØÊúâÁî®‚ù§ÁÖÆÁöÑ‰∫∫„ÄÇTHANK SO MUCH ^^~
love their scrambled egg and fried potato, mala was not too oily and flavour was really good, would eat again

Tried with my colleauges. The food was tasty with very reasonable price.
Fish head curry and Tandori chicken tasted great. Overall the portion served was great and value for money.

Customer service was very pleasant.

Great place to eat at, owners are extremely friendly and would constant check on you and engage in some light hearted conversation with you!,  food are budget friendly with a 1KG Meat platter and add on of several other ala carte dishes came to a cost of 45 for a group of 4, definitely worth it! Food was fresh and marinated deliciously, been coming back every month to support them. Can't wait to go back again ahah.

A neighborhood joint to get a quick yakiniku fix. Food wise is alright I guess. Price to portion rato is on the higher side. Service was ok. Expect to queue during peak periods; but the online queue number service was neat. While I think the quality of the standard meat selections was fair, the premium selection touted as A5 was below expectations. There was a wide variety of condiments for the choosing. Drinks were served right out of their commercial bottles. The interior is rather cramped and quite hot, thus not a place you would want to be in other than to eat and go. The relatively short timing (yes there is a dining window) also made the whole experience feel a little rushed. Do note that the buzzer doesn't ring and just vibrates. For a while I thought there were some renovations going on only to realize it was the buzzer all along, LOL. Parking is plenty in the Hub itself.
Not bad, decent Japanese restaurant with overall a 7/10 :) The beef curry was flavourful and portion was filling!

The ambience is simple n neat. No special mention to the upkeep or deco of the place.

The food we ordered were mutton biryani and mee goreng.

Food was served within 15 mins. The mutton biryani was not so special. Normal and raita was not so good. Side gravy was sambar! Why sambar for biryani?

The only saving item in e platter is the mutton pcs which were juicy n gravy was spicy n tasty.

Mee goreng was a messy wet mixture of uncooked masala n day old fried chicken pcs wt bones. Unnecessarily spicy and its a raw masala soaked yellow mee.

Overall its only good for one time try.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Not too spicy. Chicken wing is nice. Rice serving a little small though.

If I could rate this zero stars which is the rightful rating.
I should have read all the bad reviews before coming here.

Super bad attitude n bad horrible expensive food.  Paid $8/-for 3pcs of punny pork bones. The Bak Kut Teh stall guy..treated me like i owe iit to him to accept my order. And he wanted additional $$ fot soup refill.
To all tourist and locals,  my advice is NEVER PATRONISE THIS PLACE.

Walked in and placed my order at 6:45PM. Food isn't even here at 7:40PM. Waited almost one whole hour, nothing. Not even the simplest things to cook like cabbage soup. Nearby tables already got their food when they came after my table. Will not revisit again, waste of my time.
Delicious..value for money
Tofu is silky smooth and seafood is fresh. Portion is just nice. Comfortable environment for eating and fast service.

Ordered Lor Bak for dinner via foodpanda. Not sure whether the insides of the ngor hiang (beancurd meat roll) is supposed to be wet or not. Found it slightly disconcerting but finished it because it doesn't taste spoilt or weird. Big mistake. Had tummyache for the entire night then started having diarrhear and nausea since morning. Safe to say that I won't be ordering anything from there that isn't freshly cooked to order from now on.
Awesome place. One of my fave western at TPY.
The bean paste noodle was miserly in portion though price had gone up. Not only was noodles dry and clumpy, the bean sauce was small in portion , hence making the noodles "dry".

Arrived 12.35pm. There were 3 groups in front of us. Nobody seemed to be leaving the restaurant. As we were running out of time to start work at 2pm, we decided to take away. After ordering curry chicken and rice and curry chicken with bread, and one kosong prata, we were told the wait will be approximately 15mins. As we waited, we wondered why it took longer than expected.  Curry chicken and rice are precooked. Why so long? Maybe short of manpower.
The curry was good. The chicken were generous in portions. We were not disappointed.

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: Selling sushi without giving chopstick how to eat ?

Ordered Penang char kuey teow and penang laksa, both  are really good. Authentic flavor. Love the kuey teow myself. Would definitely come back for more.
Not sure why the rating is not very high, but will definitely recommend to try out the food here! :)

Deep fried to perfection. Mantou and taukee is a must!
Sauces are average, but the chilli is worth a dip.

The food was great in overall, in particular the squid and the uni hand roll. We felt that the mushrooms could have been done better, it seemed to be lacking in flavour/fragrance. The sake selection was unique. The ambience was nice! Recommended to try.

Had the Dinner Dim Sum Buffet.

It comes with abalone, sharkfin and a few other dishes on top of their free flow dim sum dishes.

However, not all dishes are worth the order.

For instance, prawn paste chicken tasted bland and felt more like a KFC crispy chicken with very very subtle/non-existent praen flavors.

Their charsiew and chicken, which si their BBQ roast, weren't nice at all. It taste more like a microwaved dish that's dried and weirdly flavoured.

Carrot cake was just average.

Sliced fish (with pork?), wasnt very nice as well.

But that's most of their bad.

So what's good?
Sharkfin literally had sharkfin in it, abalone was nicely seasoned and done. Fried beancurd prawn paste was unique, crispy and flavourful.

Their pork chop with chef's sauce is great as well.
Their spicy vinegar wonton is very nice, in contrast with the typical dim sum stores that barely had any filling, TungLok had it filled with prawn filling and very flavourful sauce.

Siew Mai were meaty and nice, worth the order for any dimsum trip.

Poached prawns are very savoury and fresh.

So is it worth another visit? Maybe? Likely not. It's refreshing to see their dimsum being served by the sushi trains u saw in Genki. But other than that, food wasnt very amazing.

Get the shengjian bao. Best I've had in Singapore. The other foods are totally legit. Menu is small so you can feel free to try everything.

Spring rolls and meicai kourou bao was amazing
Value for money. Love the crayfish hor fun!
Great food, great service. Tom yum seafood noodle is really...good!
Delicious unagi and salmon protein bowls. Service is fast because not a lot of people.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Authentic Hunan food. Used to travel to Changsha at least once a year and so miss Hunan food. Taste is very well balanced. Unexpected find was the potato with cumin that is almost addictive and takes self-control to stop eating it. The other dishes ordered are very good and satisfying.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
As I live fairly nearby, my family and I used to patronised its outlet that was located along Thomson Road.

Ever since it shifted to United Square, we have not try.

We came this afternoon and there was a Q. We waited in line for about 10 mins and was ushered to our table.

We ordered:

1. Chicken for 2pax
2. Mixed Roast pork & Char Siew
3. Prawn roll (small)
4. Sambal Kang Kong
5. Dumpling soup (6 pcs)
6. 1 plain rice
7. 1 chicken rice

Total damage: $54.15

Food reviews (subject to personal taste):

1. Normal chicken - doesn't give me the smooth texture or tasted succulent. Cucumber not even whole slices but within the big slice, sliced up even more

2. Roast pork tip didn't have that crunch which was disappointing. Char siew was little chunky sliced up and not much of charred flavour

3. Prawn Roll dish was decent for me

4. Sambal Kang Kong came out extremely salty and had to send back to change another. When returned 2nd time, it was still salty. Staff shared with sambal is such and is salty. We didn't want to comment much as for those who cook, is the amount of sauce/salt that a chef adds. Thus is adjustable.

5. Dumpling soup was decent
7. Chicken rice didn't capture the essence of chicken stock(if they use to cook)
Tasty sweet and sour pork, well plated too üëå
Yummy! The pork rib soup is nice. Herbal taste just taste great. Fried yam is great too. Really like it. Worth coming back

Excellent place with a wide variety of food !! Out of all the food places i‚Äôve tried in SG, this place sells the most affordable yet delicious Nasi Lemak.Highly recommended. Friendly vendors and a very lovely environment to dine in or takeaway. 11/10

Food delicious, and service is great. First time to try India food, and the man on the counter recommend some top rated food.Thanks for your help!
All is very nice except the one topped with chips. We really like these naans and mutton. But they are a bit pricey, among which there is one small bowl medium chicken meat, which is placed in a green bowl of diameter 6cm and that cost 6 dollars. We two adults and  one small child spent 28 dollars in total after the 10% off NTU staff discount.

If you don‚Äôt have the capacity to handle online orders, stop taking them. You are not only inconveniencing the customer but also the delivery person. Case in point, we ordered food at 5pm today (19 June) and the first scheduled delivery time was 5.30pm. Then it became 5.45, then 5.55 and 6.40pm. I am writing this is at 6.15pm. That is totally unacceptable and utterly irresponsible of Ichiban Boshi. The driver had to wait and potentially lose other deliveries because of your restaurant‚Äôs irresponsible behaviour. I will make it my personal mission to tell everyone about your ‚Äòwonderful‚Äô business.

Really cozy n beautiful place for nice Chinese fusion food.  Gd portion for ladies to share as well as the soup too. Service is excellent too n thank you for going the extra mile to get us the cake for mini celebration.

Had the shrimp omelette and seafood pad thai with thai milk tea. Although I would have liked the pad thai more spicy, it was very delicious. The mango sticky rice was really good also. The staff, Shidah and Ali, were very attentive and helpful as well :D

The service was pretty bad. I mean, we‚Äôre paying customers, not the wait staff‚Äôs debtors. Food was slightly below expectations I mean‚Ä¶ fried tofu is a pretty standardised dish. Chicken could be more tender and was fatty.

Try chicken house at upper Thomson if you want better chicken rice

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content:
Charge you extra to compensate your kopitiam card discount.
A bit expensive compared to other kopitiams.
Love the freedom to choose different vegetables or meats items with selected soup and noodles.
Consistently good. One can always count on them for a delicious meal! Black bean beef hor fun, prawn paste chicken, fish slice soup and cereal squid are the best!
Rice a bit hard

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Very authentic korean taste!! The jjajangmyeon was very good indeed! Will be back!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: This place is very crowded on weekends, especially at night. Expect to wait for 30min before finding a seat. Bookings can only be made for groups more than 10 people. The garlic chicken was our favorite dish and the beef was surprisingly tender. Paid about $13 per person.

Love the recommended dishes : Sakura Tagliatelle, Cava Burger. Food is really good, best part I can get to see beautiful fur patrons playing at the outdoor area. Didn't enjoy the lemon meringue tart though.

Inflation has taken a hit on the price and portion size and the shortage of workers is visible with only half the seating capacity opened. We waited only five minutes for our turn üòä

The cutlery is not so clean and we had to wash it ourselves.

The dessert of the cake was panna cotta which is fine. It used to be cake and we remember the cake we used to have was really good and we complimented the restaurant for it when we visited back in March.

The soup of the day was chicken soup with vegetables. Still value for money.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Serve overnight roasted duck rice. Tasteless and tough. Service is poor and staff is rude.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
For Service - * * * * (4 Stars)
For Environment - * * *  (3 Stars)
For Food Taste - * * * (3 Stars)
Out of 5 stars.

One of the better tasting prata eatery in Singapore. The prata is thin and crispy. The fish curry is thick and creamy, not the typical watery type. The mutabak is huge and good for sharing. The teh tarik is fragrant and bubbly. The fish curry is nice too. They also sell assorted Indian snacks. The price is slight higher as it‚Äôs an air conditioned restraunt. Try to avoid peak hours ie 12pm, 630pm.

Pasta is really too oily, I ordered tomato sauce pasta but it tasted like fish curry....will not eat it again. Beware of the 5 star review here, its really suspicious...Look at the queue during lunch and dinner hours and the amount of people seated, its a clear sign.
No point ordering. Tried for one hour to get my delivery. No support, nothing. Very sad as we used to like this place. Sad.

This place is not for couple. Well that's becos it serves up so many varieties of Thai food that i feel a couple will never truly be able to enjoy it's offering on the first visit..always enjoy the dishes while it's hot.

Terrible terrible food here. Ordered the briyani with Sotong and the Sotong is so hard and chewy. It tasted like it was cooked a few days ago. The rice was half cooked and was clumpy. The Maggie mee goreng is only half warm. Some parts of the noodles were cold. My drinks I asked for kosong, and I even reminded them no sugar, they added sugar to it. It was just a whole string of unfortunate food orders. Was good 15 years ago. It‚Äôs terribly disgusting now.
Most of the fried food is nice, but pricing getting higher.
Food is a total no complaint, absolutely superb. Worth of every single penny spend. Whole chicken drumstick is crazy. Chicken meat must go with their homemade dark soy sauce chilli.
You will get best butter chicken, The taste was amazing. Must try. Not so expensive and good quality.
Food cheap but tasteless, rude!

I believe this is the worst train sushi I had in my entire life. Nothing can be much worst than this. It's a total disappointment , waste of time n your stomach space.

The fried food was cold and bland. Sushi was way below average. Sushi go deserve 0 star. Whenever I need assistance, I need to walk to e counter n find staff for help.
And this one star is for floor staff Vicky. She is e one n only staff tat offer to help us clear e empty plate.
All the noodles are damn salty. Totally not worth the money. If there's a "zero" star , I would give it to this shop/cafe/restaurant without any hesitation.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: Wet market and a food court in level 2. Renovated one. Gets crowded during lunch hours. More options to eat.

First dine in after phrase 2 was over and glad that the experience was largely positive. Food was decent, especially like the HK style congee though the pig intestine was a tad too rubbery and hard to chew. Service was prompt and friendly which is always a plus. Will go back again.
5 star for food, minus 1 star for the enclosed area noise from chit chatting.

An excellent restaurant for the genre - located in a bowling alley, aimed at families, the food selection is fair, the portiin size very nice, the price is reasonable. Good for people who need baby chairs, too, which is a plus.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: The food there was delicious. The manager there , Mr Theva was very kind and attentive. My friend and i had a good time dining at suki thai !

Zichar place with aircon and a heart in what they serve. The claypot tofu is one of the best we ever tasted. Nothing to complain. Little boy loves the roasted pork inside while his daddy likes this kind of toufu very much (someone should put this as an official guideline for all Zichar places: only this kind of toufu should be used for claypot). The shrimp paste chicken has crispier skin. We tried the signature Kyoto rib in yam ring (because don‚Äôt have the vegan Assam fish that day üò≠üò≠). Rib is tender but a bit ‚Äúporky‚Äù. Prob won‚Äôt try again for that price.  Would like to recommend the hot honey lemon. Much better than expected. üòãüòã

The ambience is nice n clean , the staff there are very helpful. And the main agenda claypot chicken rice is good too. And also to add their burnt bee hoon was very nice too. Its sure worth the money to give urself a treat here..value for money..
Best Satay in Central Singapore.

Update: standard has dropped, waiting is now endless, and it‚Äôs really hard to get food decently here.

-old outdated-
Umpteenth visit to this aircon clean zhichar place with great food and reasonable prices. Ate the seafood horfun again and again.. with lovely wokhei for only $6.50. highly recommended

Lots of prawns on prawn fritters. Food arrived hot and crispy. Taste of dipping sauce was spot on. Asked for refill of sauce. Waiter obliged. Not thirsty after meal. Totally satisfied. Will only eat from them from now on.

This is apparently their clay pot noodles. First time I‚Äôve seen a clay pot noodles with soup. I overheard the service staff asking the kitchen staff why was there soup, but somehow it still was served to me. The service staff also insisted that the clay pot noodles had soup in it. Benefit of the doubt I suppose. The ‚Äúclaypot noodles‚Äù was passable. An egg was also forgotten from my order.

In the half an hour in this establishment, there was also a blackout.

Herbs-Food Prawns in Bamboo Shoot, Deep Fried Slices of Tenggui Fish, Braised Bean Curd Skin with Kailan, Heng Hwa Mee Sua, Oyster Omelette. The restaurant putien has its origins in a coffee shop and has grown to become a Michelin worthy restaurant. If you still prefer the good old coffeeshop style, this Heng Hua cuisine which still operates under a HDB is an option and at an affordable one as well.

Must try the ‚ÄúIndian claypot‚Äù dish (topped with fried egg) in this picture. That is their specialty and it seems to me local (Malaysian/ Singaporean India n) specialty. Do come and ‚ÄúTaste and see‚Äù these authentic local Indian cuisine!!

Like it especially when most of their food quality re pretty consistent at all their outlets. Fresh quality ingredients used! Extensive menu and huge serving. Always find ourselves sharing the hotpot meal. I like their ika tempura. It tasted incredibly delicious topping it off with the Wasabi Mayo! Just a note to highlight, although the service was relatively prompt, but the waiting time of the food was slightly longer than usual. Meanwhile, remember to scan your RE&S membership upon making payment if you are one too! üëçüèº

Updated with more photos on 5 April.

We found the unit price of each food item increases quite a lot, almost 20 to 30% compared to last time we came about one year ago, though they still offered 40% during 2:30 to 4:30, for 2 pax, it costs almost 100 to get just 70% full.
The service is faster this time compared to one year ago, food itself is fresh and they do have Sacha souce that is quite rare to find in Singapore.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content: The stall that sells economy beehoon and nasi lemak always has long queues as the food is very tasty and price very reasonable

Pasta, steak and veggie are quite nice.

Service not so friendly. The Auntie is quite too strict. üòÖ I don‚Äôt feel like a client.

Pricing is quite okay. I just wish can be a bit bigger serving. üòäüëçüèª

Tanoke is a recent partner to my company and also only in recent did I get the chance to head on into Tanoke to try the dinner menu with our members. Twice I've been here for dinner and once for lunch, and never once was I ever disappointed. In fact the portions are so huge for both our dinner set ($128++ or something in that range) and the portion is generous! I'm disappointed at my own shrunk appetite for not being able to finish my ricecovered in truffle shavings!

The wagyu, it melts in your mouth, the grilled lamb omg that char‚Äîgrill on it is perfect! The rice with the onsen tamago in it, and nothing but black truffle shavings on top, it's luxury at its best. And let's not forgot those appetisers that build up to the main course that you'd have thought could not get any better. Oh it does, it SO does.

I super love the sushi of uni, with ikura wrapped in crispy seaweed, with some gold flakes on top and a side of deep fried gobo shavings. It's all so good! And the portion, they're so generous with the uni that it's spilling out!

Let's not forget the dessert! The first time I was there I tasted their sorbet, not just any, but a shiso with Lychee sorbet, it's an acquired taste, but I so love how it cleanse the palate and makes you want to continue eating even more! The second time I visited, I had the gin infused jam with matcha panna cotta, speechless good. Its so silky, smooth and omg so wonderfully easy to keep eating it despite how filling all the other dishes before makes you.

If ever you need some drinks to go with your food. Everyone in the restaurant are well-versed in their knowledge of sake and could recommend good sake pairings for each of your dishes too. I love how intimate the mezzanine is, and it's just so cozy up there in the private space that I wish the night of fun dining will just keep continuing.

I'm always back for more, especially to try out their lunch menu, and omg it is so so SO GOOD! They serve mainly dons in the afternoon, but the miso soup is so good, I wish I could have just had more. And the staff are so kind to pair my grilled pork don with a glass of sakura sake.

I'm already missing the food and dishes, especially the grilled baby corns only avail in lunch! Super looking forward to going back to dine there once again!

Super disappointed by the tamarind prawn soup with vegetables (item 18A). For $15.90++, it had two tiny measly prawns. Veggies were cabbage, broccoli and carrot - which were too raw. And the soup was too spicy to drink - even though we had requested "less spicy" at the point of ordering but told that it is not spicy.

Thankfully the stuffed fried chicken wings redeemed the meal somewhat - these were juicy and flavourful. Not cheap either though.

Not great for a first experience, but we will give it another shot (without this soup).

Recommended. Authentic Malaysia Food, the standard quite consistent. Love Ëæ£Ê§íÊùøÈù¢ÔºåClaypot Chicken rice, hokkien noodles, Nasi Lemak, and Cendol here!

Updated on 6 Nov 2021: wasn't happy with the food here since last few visit. The food wasn't as tasty as it used to be, especially claypot chicken rice. And yesterday was our time tried their wan ton noodles (towards more sweetness) and fried carrot cake (towards more salty), to be more exact in Chinese.. ‰∏§ÁõòÊ≤°ÊúâÁÅµÈ≠ÇÁöÑÈ£üÁâ©„ÄÇüòÖ The dishes only "looked" authentic but the taste is below expectation. Same goes to kopi c ice. :(  was rated 5 stars in year 2019, but the food standards wasn't maintain since my past few visits.

Recommended by my friends.
I love the Mojito very refreshing
Goes well with satti Sorru chicken. FOODs is delicious. Will come back again. üòä
Soft and tasty herbal duck. the mongolian ribs are nice oo.
