A pleasant evening with family...celebrating wife's birthday. The food was incredibly marvelicious & the dessert....Superbly delicious..
Thanks to the Supv Firdaus & his team on duty wif 5stars service...will definitely recommend my friends & staff to dine again...MasyaAllah.

Came here on mother day. Full of ppl but Luckily we come earlier. The person who attend us is very good. Just like he is the only one who working like that. Give queue number. Call number, bring customer to table, help for any customer request and so on. Of course Other waiter and waitress is good also, Just lack of manpower on that day. Anyway thanks for the guy in front. U are the best. The food is very delicious. We tried the cold soba (i think this is how it call.) The teriyaki chicken set is yummy too. Will definitely come again. If u like sushi, there are so many choices. Suitable for ppl who love Japanese food.
Ordered unagi don and my mouth is literally soaked with saltiness. Small serving as well.
Terrible staff at Wadori, either not focusing and letting others cut my queue, or not telling me something from my set has run out. Gave 2 chances, both failed.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: They never giving important to dine-in customers. No proper queuing system to collect the ordered food. Ordered Mee Goreng it was worst taste and cucumber not fresh.

Samosas and pratas are really good here. Good hospitality and service from all the staff members.
Mrs. Christina helped us with takeaway with much ease

Excellent beef steak for coffeeshop western food. The black pepper sauce is not hot but just actually sweet bring out the sweetness of the beef. The mash potatoes fried ball is butter yummy. The fried rice is actually above average and surprise to find shrimp in there. However do note that the steak is not cheapt starting at 13 for sirloin and 15 for ribeye and 18 for tenderloin if I am not wrong. However one of the much better western food stall out there.
Hidden gem that offers quality food at reasonable prices. Great service from staff too!

(Translated by Google) Fine Chinese food!

(Original)
Finom k√≠nai √©telek!
Nice foods.
Claypot rice. Good taste. Next best to eating it in M'sia

Had a enjoyable lunch here. Ordering system was easy and food was served in a fast speed.
Took the lunch set with a drink, upgrade soup and upgrade dessert.
All the foods are standard and tasty but not superb. Lobster bisque was average. T bone steak was good but i got a medium well close to well done although I ordered for medium, a bit disappointed for this. The orea cheese cake was good.

Overall the food price considers to be at a slightly higher average, unless the food is super delicious. It's still a good place if you don't know what to eat as they serve quite a big range of food varieties.
Nice good and reasonable price

Staff absolutely have no idea what is on their menu and got me the wrong order for takeaway. Even the refund process took some time and I was not allowed a refund because the kitchen is already preparing my item. Total waste of time and ruin of appetite

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Love all the dishes I ordered!

A modern asian cuisine - enjoyed the food here! The roasted duck‚Äôs skin is super crispy I can‚Äôt forget how good it is! The lamb is tender and has a great flavour to it. The Seafood XO fried rice that we ordered was pretty amazing too. The atmosphere was great, pretty private, its a good place for gathering too as they have private section for bigger groups. Would highly recommend if you are into exploring new experiences.

Delicious, authentic, hearty Hong Kong style dish and dim sum, a rare gem in the city.

The baked egg yolk bun is an absolute gem, and don't miss the abalone sauce braised rice and crispy skin roast piglet. All dishes I ordered  taste spot on, quite a statement for the skill of the chef.

The decor feels oldish and the service is not as good as those fancy looking, Michelin star bearing places, but the food here tastes as good or better without the pretentiousness. It is a place where I crash into alone after work, or bring my friends to, but not for treating my business partner with fancy wine.

Sitting here I feel I'm in one of those neighborhood favorite restaurants in Hong Kong or in some Chinatown in the US with comforting dependable delicious food, what else do I want in a restaurant?

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content:
Ambience: 9/10
Food: 7/10
Service: 7/10
Price: 9/10

Previously frequent the branch at Bishan which located at a coffeehouse. It was very very humid and hot. But now they've shifted to TPY and its air-conditioned! The food is mediocre but the portion is quite big for the cheap price. Perfect fix of a meal on a rainy day!

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Attentive staff, good food, spacious and air conditioned. Better than Golden Mile outlet!

Very bad customer service, eating the main course half way they suddenly serve the desert and clear my plate as the food not finish, ask for a extra chair to put my baby stuff and bag and the staff there keep saying u block the way here and there, I already push the chair very near to my table, I'm there with my family to spend and have our nice dinner, not asking for your staff to treat us like that. Food potion is getting lesser and lesser and price is getting higher and higher. Never think about go back again as there are many other choices out there.

Review for the Hainanese Curry Chicken rice:

Overall the food was honestly not that great, the curry was meh and food was cold. Chicken was pink and I raised a concern to the guy at the stall and he said it was okay to eat, but still gave me a new one for my piece of mind so that was nice. Seats are nice and clean though and will probably try out the other stalls, just not this one.

Quite disappointed with the foods. I won‚Äôt called it the Japanese food. Fried rice is oily and bland. Curry tempura, pretty much out from the Japanese curry cubes paste. Teriyaki cod fish, not really fresh.
Don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll go back again.

Terrible service.
Waited for an hour for frog hot pot.

Only 4 tables were occupied at that time.
A table arrived 15 mins later than us, has been served their dishes.
The waitress attitude was very bad. One of the waitress actually replied ‚Äú‰∏çÁÆ°ÊàëÁöÑ‰∫ãÔºÅÈóÆ‰∏ªÈïøÔºÅ‚Äù Superior actually gave us permission to leave as they are unable to serve the dish after an hour.

NOT RECOMMENDED at all.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
We visit this restaurant often. Cos we live nearby, They've raised 5% service charge and GST since 7th April. That's fine, but they have provided lesser portion than before. Which does not justify the implementation in service charge and gst.
Very disappointed

A good place to chill, $1 loklok per stick. They provide 3 types of sauce: Satay, Sweet Chili, and their signature chili sauce. However the place is crowded during dinner, might take time to get your seat.

texture was kind of hard. the food was oily and salty, but i like the cheese~ but the customer service was so bad, and in my opinion, the worst in ntu . the uncle mixed up my order and had the audacity to say that i was the one who agreed with him? he said ‚Äú i asked you mac and cheese u still say ya ya‚Äù !!?? i mentioned that i wanted baked VEGGIE mac & cheese twice? my friend said she heard me too. still, he didnt have the decency to change my order or refund me. i had to ask for it and not a single apology.. worse, the other guy still could not understand my order. my friend and i were so disappointed by the customer service :(( we tried to be nice but it felt like they were the ones who were mad at us?

Staple dishes such as fried rice and noodles only has 1 size: personal size. Not a place for proper dinning, but more for dim sum and small eaters. Menu item seem limited. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Hope they improve on the food bit.
Have ordered their Karubi Set upsized. Meat was good. won‚Äôt have the bbq stained smell after eating. also good place for solo people. Price :$$

Lots of choices of old time favourites. My pork noodle was tasty wz lots of meat in it. Friend's fried kwayteow was a let down, no wok-hei, cockles or lap-cheong.... Claypot chicken rice was good wz chunks of chicken meat n salted fish.

Being a grad student at NTU, I have at least 3-4 meals in a month here at The Soup spoon. Being a vegetarian I mostly stick to the meatless minestrone soup. I do miss the wraps option they use to have earlier. I do like their salad,pretty simple. Wish they could increase the serving quantity slightly though. This outlet is priced lesser than the outlets outside NTU. So make the most of it.
I was also wondering if they can serve the drinks in non plastic containers when one is not taking away the drinks.

I tried the following
1. Century egg & lean meat congee
2. Ginseng chicken drumstick congee
3. Fried intestines - a let down, crunchy and tasteless.
4. Stir fried garlic dou miao

Come here if you prefer thick porridge. The set comes with fried fritter (you tiao) and soy milk (not sweet).

Best!! Love the dimsum buffet! They literally flood your table with food!! The siew mai is one of the best I have tried. With flounder powder. True teochew style. Dimsum are served hot, fresh prawns filling! Aunties are super friendly. Love the place. Will refer it to all my friends!!!!!

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: We have been to Tasty Loong multiple times as we liked their food . However, we were utterly disappointed in their food  served today. Their baked pork ribs with marmite sauce tasted like lean meat, and it wasn't tender like usual pork ribs ‚Ä¶

my #1 spot for chicken cutlet rice. auntie has always kept the price low at $3.80 and sizeable portion since i was in poly and now in uni. now got option for upsize since i brought my boyfriend hahaha.

its true to describe it as old school taste! my mum likes to buy the chicken wings that is comparable to arnolds chicken. still recommend the cutlet rice over anything!
not the first time online orders get cancelled. quality  of food found wanting compared to other branches

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: A nice restaurant at the hidden gem of ORTO in the North. The dishes were fabulous and the views were even better. Also tried their popular roast chicken and to my surprise, they actually torched the chicken in front of us before plating it. Definitely worth a visit and try.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Add a spoon of X0 for the extra kick. 3.50/spoon only! Generous amount. Solid

Good place for a yakiniku fix, food came reasonably fast even during peak hours. Shannon was quick to clear the queue and usher me and the others to our tables. Only bad thing was the bottled drinks pricing. just order their hot green tea if dining in, at least feels more refreshing when eating bbq.
6$ chicken yakisoba was served cold with only one piece of chicken, do not eat here, had food poisoning afterward
Should be one of the cheapest Western food around the area, grilled items tasted better than the fried one. Expect long waiting time during peak hours.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Quite terrible experience, they‚Äôre serving larger groups who came after us but kept smaller groups waiting it seemed, even though our order wasn‚Äôt small. Bizarrely, they‚Äôre preparing 3-4 same items and serving to multiple tables instead of handling each table in order. After long time we decided to have crab but this restaurant dashed our hopes, after almost 1 hour of waiting patiently, they gladly said they haven‚Äôt started preparing our crab, why not just tell at entrance how long one has to wait for an item. The owner didn‚Äôt give a damn when we complained about the service, obviously not bothered by losing one customer coz they‚Äôre fully packed. We were hoping to bring parents there but we are not going back .

A budget Japanese restaurant which gives good value for money. This is a busy outlet with queue number system so be prepared for a long wait on peak hours.

Another successful chain by the RE&S group.

July 2022: LOVE the durian dessert!! Unfortunately it is not often available - was really happy to be able to order it at this outlet. However, the durian paste was still frozen and too hard to eat. Had to use a lot of strength to break the durian cube apart to eat. I had it in another outlet and the instead was creamy and molten but yet still stiff enough to keep a cube shape.

Found out about this hidden gem from a Straits Times review. Ordered their BBQ pork collar (was recommended their pork neck), Tom Yum soup with prawns looked great & tasted great. And added their Thai omelette rice $5.50.

Highly recommended & way superior to anything you can find at Thai enclave at Golden Mile. So authentic, cook is Thai. Legit!

Standards are slowly but surely dropping. I don't mind paying a higher price for fresh, crispy prata but I hate it when they serve me pre-made ones. Made the decision to order Masala Thosai, it was good, with generous amount of potatoes sandwiched between crispy Thosai. Its weird that they served me with only Dahl curry instead of an assortment. Their teh tarik was tasteless on the day of my visit too. This my 3 stars.

Edit: contacted the hotline as requested by the business owner. Was updated that the branch ran out of the other condiments on the day of my visit. They offered me a free Thosai on my next visit which I turned down. Nevertheless, was heartened by the business owner's willingness to receive feedback. Kudos to them! Have upgraded my 3 stars to 4 stars because of this.
Fantastic food, great service, very clean and hygienic makan place and reasonable price. Staff is friendly, owner is very welcoming. Food variety and quality , 2 thumbs up !!! MUST TRY !!!

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Valuable meal whole chicken $9.90. half chicken set $8.80
Always spoilt for choice with the spread on offer that varies daily. My favourite is the pumpkin. The battered cauliflower and meat dishes are also good.

Went during lunch hour.

Ordered the xiao long bao and the spicy noodle.

Xiao long bao‚Äôs meat was thick like the normal meat bao. And the noodle‚Äôs soup is quite tasteless, the meat in the soup are just pork cubes.

The upsides are the food are prepared on the spot and came hot. And they are quite affordable.

However also to note during my visit, the staff asked me to leave to make way for a group of customers that just came in without enough seats. I havent finished my drink at that point. So that wasnt pleasant. They could have managed it better.
Filipino joint in novena, worth checking out

Bought take away - 2 x clear tom yum seafood with 2 rice. It Used to be above average hence it‚Äôs once of my options buy dinner or once a while dine in.

When I reached home, I was shocked that the seafood portion in it was so little, just 3 small prawns and a few sotong (used to have fish), used to have mushrooms and tomatoes but this time round 2 tiny mushrooms and small slices of tomato. And then lots of soup and then that‚Äôs it‚Ä¶

$9 for this amount is clearly unacceptable.

I doubt i will be returning to eat here again. Standards drop and really felt shortchanged üò§
The famous spring chicken

Two of us had lunch here. It actually inside the Tunglok Seafood Restaurant. The food served was fresh and nice especially Sashimi. The service staff was also attentive and helpful. Great experience! Will visit again!

Nice.... Alot of food to choose but is got limited time for each food

Like prata start at 7am until 12pm then it's start sale again at 4.00pm

Same a goreng start at afternoon

Chapati and naan start at evening

Ordered the $108++/pax set dinner. Gone are its glory days when it's food is mind-blowing in terms of taste & creativity. To be fair, then it was still a private dining place, and it was more than 10 years ago. I was so wow that I went to the HK branch when I was over there.

Now it is just an ordinary restaurant dishing out boring fusion stuff. It's execution can be better as well. The only ok dish was the platter. The best is the soaked cherry. But this was an early creation since private dinning days, except that it has shrunk in size.  The rest of the dishes were so under-whelming. 1 star is for the food. One main reason was that the food tasted like a typical Chinese restaurant. Why would I pay so much to eat something so ordinary. Xi Yan ‰∏çÂÜçÊòØÊòîÊó•ÁöÑ Xi Yan, ÂèØÊÉúÂèØÊÉú„ÄÇ

The service was good; attentive & friendly staff.

Amazing charcoal flavour on the skewers!
The staffs are really friendly and would give recommendations when we were unsure of what to get.
Worth the price. You get what you pay for and more

I went into the cafe during weekend lunch. Waited 5 mins for someone to direct to be seated then I had to asked the staff who is just solely doing the coffee whether we could sit at the table. Then we sat down for 5 mins look through the menu and decided what we wanted to eat and raised my hand to ask to order and another staff saw my hand so I put down my hand. Then after awhile thinking that the staff would come over to take my order but he disappeared. So after searching for the person and waiting for someone to come and take our orders for 5 mins. We decided to leave. Service is HORRIBLE. Wasted like 15mins.
Cheapest jiao zhi / wo tie you can find in Singapore. Very popular amongst the PRC community. The rice dishes came in large portions.

(Translated by Google) Nice, sweet chili. Singapore Nasi Padang.

(Original)
Nice, sweet chilli. Singapore Nasi Padang.

Food was quite mediocre. Most flavourful thing on my table was the rice seasoning. Salmon sashimi was not cut properly. Miso soup and chawanmushi was bland. Even the shoyu wasn't very pleasant. Portion was good but taste needs a lot of improvement.
Ate there for dinner, lovely tables and air conditioning

Went there for takeaway and wanted to buy fried rice, they said only got prata so i ordered that and 5 mins after i ordered the guy decided to clean the area before preparing my food which took me 45 mins of waiting time and the worse part is that in the middle of waiting i saw a guy holding the fried rice i initially order for takeaway. Overall v bad experience similar thing happen to me before at the same shop

For me it is nice food Because it is vegetarian food for me.
Staff are all nice talking and Serving. Food and price are reasonable.
just a simple old school western meal. will prefer it to be less salty.
Service is great and had a good time there. Not rushing and nice food ÔøΩ ‚Ä¶

26/05/18
Slightly above average and pricey Cha Siew and roast pork rice. The dark sauce is nice but the meat portion is too small to fill the stomach. The chilli sauce is nice too. Seriously need to improve their customer service.

Really nice place with nice ambience. The staff there are very friendly and professional as well! Definitely a good hidden corner in ntu for a getaway from campus life to enjoy some fine dining. Food is nice as well, love the jalape√±o poppers!!! Rare to see such a dish and it was done superbly well. Will highly recommend to check out this place! Do try the wagyu burger as well, and the lava cake and pecan pie are off the charts.

I am not a big fan of Chinese food but I have to say, this is one of the most satisfying lunch I hand for a very long time.

I wanted noodles with lots of vegetable options. When I look through the menu, the tofu noodles catches my attention and  so I place the order with the plum drink and the black fungus starter.

Never I expect to be surprised by the balance taste of the noodles. It was really really good. I never thought I could finish such a big bowl considering the size of it.

The starter is another pleasant surprise, so crunchy and I love every bite of it.

I will definitely be back for more....

Ordered cabbage wrapped chicken, marmite pork, French bean with minced meat and pineapple fried rice, for delivery.

The cabbage wrapped chicken is unique and hidden with some chestnuts, wolf berries, etc.
Long cooking made the cabbage soft and disintegrated with a tinge of sour taste.
Overall not bad but the chicken is a little bland.

Marmite pork is disappointing. Marmite taste and flavour is not there.
Maybe due to long delivery time, the pork is soggy but this should not affect the marmite taste though.

Pineapple fried rice is okayish but bland.

Maybe it will taste better and yummier if dine in.
Awesome prata as always. *Don't change it! Yes, I like fried chicken briyani too üëç
They had alot types of prata like cheese prata and chocolate prata. Very nice üëå

A no frills restaurant in Toa Payoh. Situated just below OrangeTee building makes it very convenient for people to access. A nice place for a meal especially for the lunch crowd.

Food was ok. Good value as we often go for the set lunches. Option to upgrade to lobster bisque should really be considered as the lobster bisque is nice. Baked potato with kits of onions and sour cream is great too.

Owners were warm and friendly.
Fries were packed separately so that they won't be soggy after the tapao journey.
Food is above average so i will go back again.

Was disappointed with their menu selection. Imagine the four of us had to order every single dish on the menu to have enough to eat! So sad that COVID had hit this restaurant so badly that they had to diminish their menu to so small.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Great ambience & environment! Favourite place for my lunch time as it's only walking distance. The staff are cool üòä Price also worth so much! So recommended üëç
This place is run by Thai folks. Quite authentic. For the price, the food is reasonable. Be prepared to wait abt 15mins for your food during lunch peak hour.

Only takeaway. Price is about the same as a restaurant - perhaps due to the excessive packaging. Quality of food is good. Would have given it 4-5stars if price is more friendly given that it is located in a heartland.

Great food, great ambience, and really great customer service especially from waitress Angela. We appreciate the pleasant experience. The customer service team was distinctly a few grades above any other restaurant that evening. Kudos to Angela for being really thoughtful and offering to charge when she knew that our phones had run out of battery. Would definitely come back for the customer service. Give Angela a raise already! haha

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content: The food was much better before. Still, for the price and the range of dim sum they offered, worth a visit if you are in the area.
Love the gam heong fried rice!

Despite its odd sounding name, this restaurant is worth a visit. It serves spicy mala Sichuan dishes.

The odd sounding name has to do with them serving bull frog as one of their signature. We had the chicken hotpot and added ingredients like beef, noodles, and vegetables. Although we asked for less spicy, to us, it was still very spicy so for those of you who are not so tolerant of spicy food, beware!

We also ordered some bbq skewers - beef, mutton, pork belly, chicken üêî ... all were tasty and nice.

We will be back to try their bbq fish and also their signature bull frog hotpot.

Recommended!
Pretty average dishes. Nothing special that really stands out. Lots of variety to choice from though. 5 dishes total price at 130 SGD including one pot of chinese tea.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Pratas good...iddly too...fish and mutton curry got standard...normally get some vege or marrow or meat in curry...efficient staff.
First time trying out their Asam Laksa and prawn noodles, pretty alright.

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content:
Your briyani is taste good but too much oil. Half of the briyani and prawn masala I throw because of high oil . Please it‚Äôs a health matter please correct it immediately.
This is not happening one time ‚Ä¶. More than 2 time . Currently I am not prepare to purchase any briyani from you. Hope you change this as soon as

Really nice interior! Went there pass the happy hour, the food can get quite pricey although the portion was definitely worth the price. The salmon mega don was really big and the salmon slices were quite thick. Would recommend to try that!

One of my favorite Cantonese restaurant in town. They hv moved from Craig Rd to Maxwell Chambers Suites. The new venue of their flagship outlet is more spacious n cosy in a convenient downtown location. N there's is an added bar serving good range of cocktails n hard liquors. As usual, staff r very friendly n attentive, service is excellent.

Friendly boss and servers. The clay pot chicken is a must order dish followed by that demure looking spicy crab soup which blows my nose away. Found another good dinner near my residence. Tables are a bit limited and not much interior deco. The food is the main star. Oh the bru coffee n masala tea is good! Will definitely come to try all the other dishes soon.
Services were still good, however it may be a little slow or required multiple attempt to capture the personnel attention. Food items offered are still of high quality.

Order the popular lobster ü¶û porridge and some recommended dishes, very flavourful and the lobster is very fresh.. the oyster ü¶™ egg is also nice üëçüèº. Do take note that the place do not have sheltered carpark nearby.

Was previously an avid fan of obba.jajjang but after I visited this place!! I‚Äôve never visited obba!!!
Their price point is more affordable than obba $11 for Jajangmyun (didn‚Äôt take note for the tangsuyuk and jam pong) but other than it‚Äôs price it‚Äôs one of the best Jajangmyun I‚Äôve ever had!! (Even compared to those I got delivered to in Korea). You can tell that the sauce was home made (or at least I feel so) because it‚Äôs light and had a unique flavour. The jjampong also blew my mind with its milky seafood broth. The tangsuyuk is to die for esp with the portions and ingredients. I love the black fungus they generously added in!!
I think overall what I‚Äôm most impressed about is that most food I eat outside (obba included) leaves me thirsty however for mukkja amazingly it doesn‚Äôt!!

I even brought over my parents who hardly live outside food out and they approved!!!

Only have good things to say about this restaurant and would recommend to anyone who wants to have a good hearty bowl of Korean Chinese food.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content: Visited on a weekday night 8pm. Ordered the set for 2 pax with spicy fried chicken cubes. The chicken cubed was delightfully crisp yet tender to Bite into and were flavourful. The Jjampong noodle was brim-filled with seafood but atad more wok-hei for the soup broth would certainly have brought the overall taste a level higher. Jjajƒ´ang noodle was slurpy and gd to have nothing much to comment nor complain abt since nt much ingredients for this noodle. Overall liked the service and overall foodfare and reasonably priced for korean noodle place in sg. Total paid $60 for 2 pax that will probably feed 3 so will recommend if one is in the area and craves korean Chinese food.

It's a nice place to dine, nice food, chicken rice, sweet sour pork, fried tofu, egg omelette with prawn, all tasted very nice. Nice comfortable location, it's a residential area and it's quiet, thanks

Food wise it is good but drink wise I find the teh halia not enough ormph. The chicken curry is good but the fish curry is a bit let down as I find it missing the depth of flavor that I always look for in a nice curry.

We ordered the Tasha Special Murtabak ($15). It is FULL of ingredients. It has cheese, mutton, ham, egg, mushroom, capsicum and tons of other stuff. Surprisingly it goes nicely together. 5 stars here.

The mee goreng is the wet style. It spicyness level is there and it has nice chunky potatoes and tau kwa. It has a thick sauce coating every strand of the noodles. Nice!

Not too bad.  For those who frequent Penang and familiar u will know that it is not fully and truly authentic Penang food. At least it is somewhere convenient when one need a quick fix of a simulation of Penang food.  Just makan makan for fun ok lah.

Food is ok. Basically just Tze Cha food. Unfortunately the service standard needs to be improved. I get the sense that servers here are either highly stress or just unhappy with their work. There was no one in the queue. I was very very polite when I approached them but they were not welcoming, and seems to be rushing me to make my decision.

It was lunch time and I just ordered a one dish meal and again, they don‚Äôt seem to be please with my small order.

After seating now, I was asked to shift my seat due to distancing breach with their neighbor stall even though I was sitting in a seat marked ‚Äúallowed‚Äù. After shifting I turned and notice another 2 tables who are very close to each other. Both gentlemen eating (more dishes than me) and they did not ask them to change table or position.

I won‚Äôt come back again. It feels like I owe them a living.

My 2nd visit n this time I brought my family along. Enjoyed all the dishes while seated in the airconditioned area. The service from the staff is once again  great n staff is courteous n patience. Highly recommended.
Sooo slowüò¢ I am starving and have to wait for more than 30 mins.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Worst vendor , have to wait more than 40 minutes for Foodpanda delivery for just 2  items, although no customers around 3 pm , still the preparing is very very slow,  seems like the staff  have no urgency. Sighhhhh..what a waste of time and pity the customer ordering the orders have to wait more than 1 hr

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Old school chicken rice restaurant. The roasted version is especially good with the sauce. The white version is very smooth.
Yummy Roti Prata and Fish Curry goes together so well. Set Briyani Rice not bad too. And milk tea so delicious.

I have to say that I really enjoyed the ramen at this little joint Takagi. Expect to wait as it‚Äôs a small place. I ordered the tantanramen with extra spicy, which is really delicious. Even the gyoza was tasty. The experience was like one of those little eateries in Japan and you have to order through the machine at the entrance. Will definitely come back again when I have ramen craving at anytime as this place opens 24 hours!
A treasure hidden within the HDB estate! Quite nice and balanced taste.
The Thai. Food is very delicious. You'll can go for a try.

ordered the bryani mutton.  the bryani rice is quite light on the spices fragrance. generous amt of mutton meat.  it's meat on bone which i like.  its tender enough. curry gravy was flavorful.  overall i would say the dish is good, but not outstanding. i would say the best in amk. when i was there, two staff were talking and they appeared not keen in taking my order.  after they're done talking, one of them then ask for my order.  the cashier is polite. dish cost 7.50 but for the amt of meat and rice, it's reasonable. will buy again.

Stopped by at Curry Times operated by the Old Chang Kee Group. Was looking forward to a curry bun filled with aromatic, rich and tangy curry that made their puffs so popular in the early 1970s. The bun was a soft and sweet but the small dollop of potato, chicken and curry mixture wasn't much to go around. It tasted like the result of mechanization. Still an amicable afternoon tea snack if you wash it down with the "kopi".

This place is always packed with hungry diners. However, the quality and taste can be rather inconsistent. Ordered their beehoon goreng twice. The first time was simply delicious. Fried to perfection. Sadly, the second time i ordered it was terrible. It was so salty that I left without touching much of it. A total waste of money. To be fair, the Indian rojak was good. The rojak sauce either make or breaks the overall satisfaction. The sauce was spicy and the consistency was just right. Would recommend the Indian rojak. Please give a 'LIKE' for this review ya. Thanks
Great Food. Appetising. Great setting.
Good affordable price

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Place is alright, unfortunately service is really poor. Tried to get the waiter‚Äôs attention but they ignored me despite making eye contact with me. Also, not sure why such establishments do not offer tap water? Wouldn‚Äôt recommend and wouldn‚Äôt return in the future

Food is really fresh and they current have a 1st anniversary deal which is attractive!

Plenty of seats available and can order directly from phone at my seat and make payment

Had the double beef zen from roman tei,  personally like it a lot ü§©

nice cozy place to eat steak within the neighborhood area.

food is decent and service is good .

place is small but cozy .

extensive menu ‚Ä¶ i had steak , decently done  to my liking .

take note no credit card payment . paylah! ok .Nets ok .

recommended.

part 2:

back again , this time back to try breakfast !

decent for the price and portion !

recommended!
Best prata n others foodüëç

1st visit here since we moved to this vicinity. Lor Mee tastes like Ban Mian with a lighter touch & okay soup base. Fried bee Hoon was dry and rather bland. Best is their See Hum blood cockles drenched in raw spicy garlic and sweetish sauce.
I always buy chicken mushroom puffs when I pass by
Quality has gone down the hill. They pre fry too many pratas and wait for people to order so it's already cold and tough. Not worth going back
Good western stall to get some pork chop.
Food is decent, price is at the higher side.
Worst food ive ever eaten...

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
mookata now opens at 12pm on all days
the food is super cheap really worth the money

Small eatery.
Food is good, rivals restaurant standard, but prices are low like coffeeshop zhi char.
Nice to find such quality food within a HDB estate

We decided to dine-in after picking the kids up from classes (adhering to 2 per table restrictions due to Covid restrictions). The Aglio Olio is very flavorful with a hint of lemon which makes it refreshing and not overly rich.
We also tried the Barramundi Fish & Chips and I loved it. The batter was very crispy and tasty. The fries were normal, but the best Barramundi fish I‚Äôve had, I feel that they‚Äôre way better than some of the restaurants I‚Äôve tried before.

I used to patronize the branch at Bugis, which had closed for business. I am glad that they still have this shop operating. If you are driving, you need to park the public car park across the road or the Duxton area. l love the Chinese pizza and boiled or pan fried dumplings, coupled with vinegar and ginger strips. If you do have appetite for sweet dessert, you may consider their pan fried red bean or lotus paste pancakes.

I have chosen restaurants in Singapore to visit again when my son fly back to Singapore and this place is one of them. It is our third visit after being strongly recommended by my friend. It is not typical dim sum but I like all their dumplings. Especially the fried dumpling is the one that all our family members liked the best, while I picked their signature steamed dumpling and my husband picked the Chinese pizza.  It did not disappont me again. So happy to visit ther with my son.
Very clean and hygienic. Staff know the ingredients of all the items on the menu. So it's easy for vegans to make good choice of their salad bowl. Very good pricing too. Love the options in tofu.

Finally tried this famous stall as the queue was short today. Had the basic mee rubus and had it packed home. The uncle was nice in asking whether I wanted my noodles and sauce packed separately, which was much appreciated as my journey home was quite long.

I finally ate it some 45 minutes later, so the noodles were understandably slightly soggy. Quite a lot of noodles and the gravy was smooth, though not much tau kwa pieces or bean sprout to help cut through the cloyness of just eating noodles.

Perhaps next time I should try having it there.
nice fish and seafood soup, reasonably priced

Authentic Thai food.
My top favourites are:
1. Grilled pork neck, very juicy.
2. No88A prawn yellow curry is a must too.
3. Omelette Cha-om

Excellent food quality at decent prices!

Must try:
- Horfun
- Curry Slice Pork Rice
- Ee-mee Stir Fried
- Claypot Tou-foo
- Deep Fried Pork Cheek

Fell way below my expectation but has the potential to be great if some changes are made.
The pork ribs were cooked just right and had plenty of smokey flavour. What let it down was the amount of bbq sauce - too little and barely having any sweetness. The meat marination also needs work. It tasted very flat. Just smoky and very salty with not much other flavour to give it depth so it got sickening quite quickly. Ratatouille was microwaved - film on the sauce and some parts of the dish were piping hot while other parts were not even warm. It marred the experience of an otherwise pretty decent side dish.

Loved the hana bara chirashi! Portions were super generous and sashimi was fresh! The flowers were a nice touch and tasty too (hana can mean flowers in japanese) üå∏

The ‚Äònormal‚Äô portion was maybe 50% bigger than the mini one. I was stuffed from the mini portionü§∞probably would have trouble finishing the ‚Äònormal‚Äô portion myself.

Will be back to try the other chirashis üòã

Edit: Went back for round 2! üëè Had the hana uni bara (mini), chirashi, and hana bara this time. The uni is sooooooo creamy and fresh!

Chirashi tastes as good as it looks. The chutoro, swordfish, yellowtail, salmon, uni, anago, flounder, ebi‚Ä¶ just wow ü§©

Favorite chirashi place üòç

Food was tasty. We had kungpow chicken, chicken was tender and flavors were good. The claypot meesua didnt really taste like meesua. It was more like ee mian, so it was a little out of our expectations. Also ordered some stir fry veg with garlic. The wok hei wasnt strong enough so it was just average. Service was a little slow but bearable.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: The restaurant keeps making mistakes by not giving full order. Once forgot to give vada with Pongal and pickles with curd rice. Also the number published is not in use. So beware as they r cheating customers

2nd table seated, but had waited an hour or more for food to be served. It seemed like they cared more about fulfillment of the Grab food orders since we had to wait so long. Even tables after us gotten some of their food first, this was made even more unpleasant with my hungry children.

What we ordered:
Basil pork with rice - first impression was terrible, serving of pork was also little, egg white was cooked too long as it was rubbery, though the sauce was okay. You can probably get better ones from coffeeshop Thai food stores which I used to get at Ubi.
Phad Thai - serving was small, really small. I also found the fish sauce lacking and this was supposed to be a chef recommendation
Pineapple fried rice - still ok, serving was "average". My kid could finish this, so it's "average" as there is always leftovers at other Thai food stores that we visit.
Fried Kway Teow with Beef - kiddo say ok not bad. Was alright but didn't tried the beef and once again serving was "average".
Tom yum (creamy) soup with seafood - ok, soup was the saviour. But I gotten a piece of squid that was mushy and was disappointed.

Overall, ok to eat but never will patronise this outlet given such waiting time for such food. Several better stores that serve much faster than this. Not hungry children friendly, but instagrammable with their signature neon sign
Another restaurant with good food and service. Good choice for a business lunch as the wait staff are well trained and Super attentive. Favourite dish was the tomato starter!

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Been wanting to try this place for the longest of time but unfortunately they do not operate on the weekend plus this place is kind of out of the way from my office. Tried going there once after work but they were already closed for the day. Apart from this shop, I believe they also do catering.

Happen to be running some errands around Tai Seng and decided to check out this place.  It was already closed to 2pm when I reached. There isn‚Äôt any crowd. Dish selection was quite limited as well. Managed to choose 3 dishes, Ayam goreng, stir-fried cabbage and begedil.  I paid SGD$6.50 which includes a can drink.

Food was delicious, Ayam goreng was crispy and it was topped with the crispy bits. Meat was tender as well. Begedil was also quite nice. Pricing wise, quite reasonable for me. This stall is quite accessible, about 5 mins walk from Tai Seng Mrt station. Should come earlier if you want to have more dishes to choose from.

Had food poisoning after ordering chirashi don from foodpanda last night. Delivery time was alright. Tuna didn‚Äôt taste fresh. I hope merchant is more careful on handling the food as this experience is really upsetting!

Food is good but bad service. Restaurant was pretty empty but food took half hr because they kept packing food for the grab orders. Only served us when my mum asked how long more. Feels like they prioritise online orders more than people who make an effort to come to the shop.
Not bad the quality

The dishes we ordered tasted good generally. Similar to other reviews, customers in queue were not seated even though there were empty seats during weekend dinner hours. Service staff without smiles, unlike traditional Thai places.

This cafe is pretty near my place but first time trying. Reservations is recommended especially for weekends. Surprised that the indoor dining area was so big.
Found the price of the food quite expensive. Breakfast for 3 easily exceeded $100. They had a promo with Citibank but we had lots of problems with it as it couldn't accept applepay or if the credit card is stored inside the phone without the full 16 digits.
Order a few dishes to share, the one we enjoyed most is the Chicken and Croffles. Both croffles and chicken were well cooked. The Roffles platter was interesting because of the rosti waffles and also liked the way the mushrooms were cooked.
Service was very slow. Not sure if they forgot the order or what. The staff are all very young and had to call them over a few times to check the status of the dishes. The sides came almost last, the Spicy Chicken wasn't really nice it didn't taste Korean but the sauce more tasted like the Thai sweet Chili sauce. The Sakura Cream Tagliatelie also came late and serving was very small which left us unsatisfied.
Drinks were just pretty average.
Really need to improve on the speed of the food served. Not sure why the cafe wasn't even crowded at all early in the morning.
The dry chilli ban mian is good. Flavourful sauce with thick, chewy noodles.

Make a reservation so that can save time in waiting.
Food is served very fast and swift.
Loves the fresh cockles with its lotsa garlic that is seasoned so well.
Sweet and Sour Pork is crispy and tasted great.
Steamed Sea Bass is Fresh and meat is tender.
Fried Toufu is so so soft and delicious.
The Xing Hua Bee Hoon and Lor Mee have that nostalgic taste.
Fried Yam is well crispy and soft.
Overall taste is like the Putien Restaurant and price is simply half of it.
Tried the whole spring chicken ($9) and chicken chop ($6). Pretty good portion size and tasted OK. Spring chicken could have been fried a bit less

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Same style as suki ya but with thai flavours. The service was a bit slow at first, but after that it was excellent and attentive. The food is great for the price. Best place to be for cheap buffet. You can't beat this restaurant based buffet at these prices.

(Translated by Google) The cashier's attitude is not good or fast. I told him cheese fries, but when I packaged them back, they only gave me fries and no salad. Also pay extra. really let me down

(Original)

I m not sure what the hype is all about. There seems to be always a queue. I ordered the chicken chop and it comes with a small portion of chicken. Taste is normal. Old school condiments eg. French fries,coleslaw, baked beans and a tiny leaf of lettuce. At $6 is about on the low side but with smaller portions, that is about right pricing. Overall can eat if around this area and feel the urge.

We had the Tonkatsu Special and Chasu Tonkatsu. Decent ramen bowl that I wouldn't mind coming to eat again. While definitely not the best bowl of ramen you can get, but considering this is located in a neighbourhood kopitiam with kopitiam level price, I would say it is well worth the price for a restaurant level dish.

I'm not sure is the workers' attitude or lack of ingredients .. We were there to get our supper last night. Ordered mee goreng.. Maggi goreng.. Fried rice.. Sup kambing and nasi briyani. Mee goreng had nothing in it.. Just plain noodles with dark soya sauce.. Not even a stripe of beansprouts or vege..not even with sambal.. N yet tasteless at all.. We all were very very surprised n dissatisfaction with the food. Eat halfway n end up in dustbin chute. Haven't mentioned that each of the food was priced at 5-6 each. Sorry to say even hawkers economic noodles looks n taste better. Sup kambing was just spiced with water, only 4pieces of small cut of meat in the Sup..n not to mention was full of grease. Chicken Briyani rice just don't feel like it..to cut the bad time short.. Too harsh to say.. We hope you may cheat us that night... But hope that others will take note. That's our first and last. Next time we definitely go for McD. Thanks

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Another visit: another one of those promo dish.. Fried duck a la orange... Absolutely scrumptious. üòä

Revisit: The lamb ribs isn't so good anymore... Sadüò≠
The meat tasted dry n leathery.. Rkn consistency is an issue.

Previous review: Typically I'm not a big fan of Aston. I eat at this location because it's convenient and I can get Safra discount. Generally the grill meats and pasta are so so, with the grilled seafood somewhat better.

Occasionally Aston do deliver some special promo dishes that's a bit more appetitising than normal, and this is what caught my eye... Moroccan lamb short ribs. It was pleasantly surprise for me as usually they tend to overdo on the meats but this lamb ribs is really worthy to command 4 stars. Nicely  charred, with a thick layer of yummilicious fats over laying tender and juicy pink meat. Grilled to medium doneness, the taste of the pinkish meat is simply delectable with natural sweetness and a subtle tinge of Moroccan spices (could be heavier with the spices if I was the cook). Leave the pepper sauce alone. It's too heavy and will overwhelm the natural taste of the spiced lamb. I must have had my month's fill of charred lamb's fats at 1 sitting but heck, it's just melts in your mouth. Too tempting to resist..YoloüòÅ, will take a couple of motilum when I get home.  üòÜ

As a purchase with purchase, I opted for the escargot baked in garlic/olive oil. That's brilliant too. Aston shd seriously consider make this lamb ribs a permanent part on their menu. I'll definitely patronise more frequently. At $19.90 a pop, this lamb ribs is great deal! üëçüëçüëç
really did not disappoint me the food is delicious and the service style is very enthusiastic‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§
Comparable taste to other similar stalls but has quite a lot of customers.

Really great food! Service was great! Would like to commend the staff, especially Shidah and Ali who really provided great service and were very patient with my queries. Didn't get the name of the other staff on duty, but she was also really helpful with my queries. Loved the food, especialy the Pad Thai, and green curry. The omelette was excellent, and their mango sticky rice was  really tasty! Will definitely return, and strongly recommended to others.

First time here. Ordered 4 of their signature dish. Was so impressed with the quantity, quality and price of the dish that I signed up their membership. Will come back for more and hope to share more detail
Ordinary, but service was good

I usually like this place, the food is very nice but yesterday was a bit of a disaster. I think they are understaffed, the scan qr menu didn't work so a member of staff took the order from the menu. Seemed to cause alot of problems, we started to get orders from other tables and nobody knew what we ordered for the whole meal. Staff were trying to solve the issue but we're very stressed out, we had to keep explaining what we ordered even though they took the original order down on paper. Had to keep asking for things also, no discount or anything offered when paying for the trouble :|

Staff were nice enough and willing to help but I probably won't go back.
A authentic taste of Malaysian Food. Gotta be best Malaysia Boleh outlet in term of taste and variety. Not easy to find seat but its all worthwhile

Great Service Chinese Teochew 'Authentic Restaurant Very classic.
Food was great Especially the Fresh Fish Steamboat
Deep fried Prawn Rolls and Braised Duck was Tender and flavourful.
Cold Crab was great
Overall Very impressive
Hidden behind Lor 8 Toa Payoh Market

We have been frequent this small eatery since yrs ago. One can never misse the Curry Chee Cheong Fun, either topped with shredded chicken or pig skin. The pig skin curry  is unique as we do not really get it easily here. It was deep fried then stewed with curry sauce which turned it soft yet retained the chewy texture. Curry sauce is really thick and aromatic. The CCF was tender, when soaked in curry sauce, one just cannot stop eating it until finished. The thin Hor Fun Noodle Soup has clear soup, mild chicken soup taste,  suitable for young kids who cannot take spicy food. Nasi Lemak is ok only, not really fantastic, the sambal is more on sweet side. Asam laksa is not really sour after sweetened. Broth is not very thick,  taste average. Curry Mee has the most generous portion with pig skin,  boneless chicken thigh pieces, tau pok and sliced fish cake. I changed yellow noodle to vermicelli which absorb the curry sauce more. This bowl of noodle is very satisfying and value for money. Coffee is not really nice if compared to the one we had in Ipoh.
I like their Mee Soto
Taste good. 3 dashes (photos) + 2 drinks and 2 rice at about $40. Will try again!

(Translated by Google) Alhamdulillah, anyone who is close to Jurong East if they are hungry can try .. Good stuff doc ..

(Original)
Alhamdulillah, sesiapa yang dah dekat Jurong East tu kalau lapar boleh cuba.. Barang baik dok..
A bowl of chirashi which clearly had a lot of thoughts put into all the ingredients. Will be back!

We came at 11.10, and food was served around 11.40. Its worth the wait. I ordered sotong cereal..oh my the cereal was soft and crispy. Hint of chilli not overpowering. The claypot rice portion is generous for two person. Two dishes and one sour plum drink came about $29. I will visit again!!

Fast, clean. Slightly advantage in the varieties,  so can order what your personal  that you like.

Fast sushi but good place to have decent peaceful catch-up meals without rushing in a busy shopping centre environment.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Good makan place n chill out

Seems like many bad reviews.  I ate once at the stall and do a take out once.

Eating there is perfect. Waiting time was acceptable. maybe about 5-10min? Food served warm, condiments was all at the side table. Chilli powder, wasabi and soy sauce. Egg onsen was ok, beef was good as this is a coffee shop. Agree is more expensive but Wagyu beef and it tasted good. I don't mind paying for it..

For take out, it dries out a little for the rice but thats acceptable.  They gave me soup also. Packaging was good. No leakage.
These 'macha' are friendly. Crowd magnet. Food rating is 8/10. I just like the ambience where you can lepak with buddies for 1 or 2 teh tarik. Not too much ah.. Must take care of health oso
Not to mention poor attitude. Fly found in fried carrot cake! Terrible!
Come and try.. üëç
Decent to good standard Indian food. Slightly on the pricier side.

I‚Äôve visited quite often here because of few reasons those closed to me, always satisfied with food quality n taste, and quickly serve the order.

Parotta and kurma best options, however, not a big fan of samosa as I don't like curry.

I and my friend and the kids dined for lunch today. It was the first time in our lives that a restaurant server can speak rudely. We found a hair strand in the tom yum soup after having 2 spoons‚Ä¶. She was insisting that its a lemongrass strand‚Ä¶ because she could not find the hair strand in the tom yum soup. She kept saying seeing is believing‚Ä¶ After all that fiasco that took place, i happened to find the hair strand and there was no sorry or whatsoever from her. The way she spoke to us is not nice at all. She even mentioned that she will not remove the tom yum soup from the bill. We clearly told her its not about the bill.. we just want to inform you that their is a hair strand inside the tom yum. We ordered alot
Of food. Surprising to hear that tone of speaking. Then while paying at the counter we spoke to the owner‚Ä¶ he did not even apologise and mentioned its a lemongrass strand. I told him i already showed your staff its a hair strand and she acknowledged it.
Waste of time to even go to such restaurants.
Service has dropped tremendously.. used to frequent this place in the past alot since funan center.
Hospitality : 0
Quality of food : 0
Pricing: overpriced
Service: 0
Taste: 0

We accidentally dropped our house key in the restaurant and only realized it when we were reaching home. That time was already after 1030pm. Luckily, the store manager was still around and she answered our call. They did pick up our keys while clearing the table. We were grateful that she was willing to stay back and waited for us to return back to the outlet to collect our keys.

Truly appreciated.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Their mutton briyani was great. The place is not too warm even on a sunny afternoon. Generally a long queue during lunch hour.
Nice food and friendly STAFF !ü§ó
The foods and service was awesome will reccomend to my friends üëç

The good taste of their food is well maintained.
But,prices of food served have gone up quite a bit.
So, do not be surprised. It's inflation.
Very nice variety of food selection, from vegetarian, egg, chicken, fish, goat, duck. Definitely good for dinning in group.

I'm on the hunt for the best Mee Soto place in Singapore ever since my favourite place closed down in 2017 (Palmer Road)

Found this place in a few food blog/vlog and was highly recommended. I've tried them and definitely enjoyed it a lot!! I might be partial to the taste of the shop that's not there anymore however this is my new #1 Mee Soto place. I'd highly suggest having it there while it's piping hot :)

Tip: add that one begedel with the mee soto please..

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Very nice food the chill is the charm. Must try. Price is really affordable üòâ if know what I mean
Great

We ordered the Set D and thought it was a good deal initially but realised the fish head wasn‚Äôt even half a head. The vegetables was a little stringy and the fried udon totally inedible. Claypot rice so-so. Granted it was a delivery and so expected food to be served a bit cold but I doubt I will ever be eating there in person.

First outlet to have a self service concept. BUT I‚Äôm not entirely sure if this self service concept is going to work.

What happened was staffs basically just stood around doing nothing. 2 staffs stood at the entrance, basically doing nothing. Another stood at the self payment counter, who tried to give instructions that isn‚Äôt clear nor loud.

Further back, you have more staffs gathering together, talking among themselves, or standing behind customers, asking them if they can clear their plates the second they picked up that last piece of meat to grill.

Food wise, standards aren‚Äôt exactly comparable to other outlets, the spicy miso sauce seemed to be a lot thicker and salter; the garlic miso was quite diluted. The meats also came drenched in sauce which made for uneven and inconsistent cooking.

Management needs to look into their staffs at this outlet. If they are already this unmotivated to serve customers within their first 3 days of opening, it does not bode well for their future. Either they need a new store management who know how to handle operations, or these staffs need to go for customer service and communications training. Self service concept is not something for you to hide behind while your staffs stand in 1 corner and slack.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Chicken was SUPER tender, had a wonderful bbq flavour! Rice was fragrant and rich with coconut. It was such a joyful experience and truly worth $5.90. Portion size is just right; and definitely coming back for more!
Food is gud but the service is late....need wait take time
Very nice and delicious home cooked foods. Good service and boss Gu Ma is very polite and friendly üòÄ üëç üòä üôè

Friends suggested going to this place at Toa Payoh Lorong 8 teochew steamboat.  The soup is thick and flavourful. Fish is very fresh. Enjoyed the food there.  Place have a traditional look. Service-wise, there were good ones, and not so "attentive" ones.

Though limited menu, the food here is good. The Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ with steam bun is particularly good. Simply heavenly.

Almost few places left that you can get a nice and decent ÁîüÁÖé these days.

The homemade noodles were also nicely done.

I'll be back for Ê¢ÖËèúÊâ£ËÇâ soon.

Homely restaurant that‚Äôs a family favorite. Mushroom soup @$5.80 was served with warm garlic butter bread. Kid‚Äôs meal was fish and chips @$8, enough for a small eater. It comes with a cup of apple juice and end off with a scoop of ice cream! Always a crowd pleaser. Chicken steak came sizzling on a hot plate and potato topped with yummy sour cream, bacon bits and green onions! The service was prompt and polite. Overall, a place we enjoy good food and service with family.

I‚Äôll share what I like about here, the service crew, an old aunty, brown bronze shoulder length hair, when we ask her why isn‚Äôt the steam bao troller coming, she offered to help us get the char siew and chee Chong fan, she‚Äôs also very attentive and responsive. As for the food quality, I‚Äôd say most of their ingredients are really fresh, especially in times like this. I‚Äôd highly recommend the char siew bao and siew mai, the fried food is above average.. I wouldn‚Äôt recommend the chee chong fan, because the char siew tasted frozen, but interestingly the char siew in the char siew bao is fresh. You can tell when the meat is not fresh because they will use a lot pepper in the meat, trying to cover the taste. Har Gao has a lot of pepper, skin is thick too. Porridge is rather blend, steam pork rib is fresh thou. The sesame mango prawn roll is pretty good too, thou the mango has not much taste. We spend about 60 ish for all the food in the photos provided. If you do intend to visit, I‚Äôd recommend you to make reservations.

Surprisingly good for all the special version Prata. They gave tons of cheese inside. A little bit regret order three of them for two person. Didn't think they have so much cheese. But the flavour is good. Definitely should give it a try.
Ordered the chicken chop for takeaway. Have patronised this stall many times. Chicken chop with mushroom sauce is not bad. Old school kind of taste. Generous with chilli sauce. Service is good too.

Absolutely amazing! This was a bit of a random find on our way back from Singapore Zoo and it‚Äôs one of the best prata‚Äôs I have had in all my time travelling there. The garlic prata is especially delicious! They are the perfect combination of crispy with a nice soft centre.
I also have to say that the ice chocolate (not milo) was fantastic. I can‚Äôt have milk and sometimes that means the iced chocolate/ milos can be a bit flavourless but this one was amazing. Wish we had found it sooner on our trip.
Come here for dinner. Pretty good place for Xinghua cuisine. Simple and nice. All dishes that ordered are good.

Tapas sharing concept, you can order some big and small plates to share. It all adds up quite substantially though so probably would recommend only for occasions you are prepared to splurge more. However it‚Äôs quite. A bustling environment. Dishes are quite innovative and delicious. Best to make reservations. Service is good.

Second time eating here due to long queues since the start of the semester. Came down once we heard that the opening hours are extended to Saturdays as well(used to be closed on Saturdays).

Soup is nice, Potatoes , fish and luncheon meat etc. are fried separately.

Very clean environment, tissue box one every table. Choice of indoor(air conditioned) or outdoor seating. You will not end up with the mala smell on your clothes even if you sit inside for more than one hour.

Price is higher than most mala hotpot outside, but definitely worth it for the environment, service and quality of food.
Do join their telegram channel for special promotions. There is currently membership for discount and freebies.

Very crowded during school days, lunch/dinner hours. Queue can be very long, only one group will be able to pick the food at a time.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: One of the best Muslim food I had in Singapore. They are super generous with the portion and with reasonable price. They beef rendang was superb, soft and tender and super flavourful. All other dishes like even ayam penyet was super good and crispy. They marinate it well. I went during off peak, and I guess it is super crowded when is at peak hour. Definitely will go back to eat again!
Nice cafe concept eatery place in a hdb shophouse. Friendly and helpful service crew. Prices on the ex side though.

If only there's minus star* The rice dumplings are simply terrible. They have no respect for food at all and their profession.
Bought 5 of those dumplings home, was told that it can be eaten straight or just simply heat it up by the staff. Went home that evening, opened one, the meat was disappointing, very tough and dry, I think it was less than 1 quarter of the whole dumpling..
the rice is not cook thoroughly and tasteless... sad evening...

How worst it get?
Well, the next morning, we open the rest of the 4 dumpling, it was all the same... no, worst, 1 even spoilt just 1 overnight, that kind of set me thinking, how long have those  $#!+ been sitting there... sad morning..
It cost $4/pc, totally not worth.

Called in to complaint, asked for management, the staff simply say: "I don't know, I don't know" part of their training? ü§î

Conclusion:
Terrible food, terrible people, terrible business...
Not bad steak was pretty well done ‚ò∫Ô∏è

@ichibanboshi.sg has an extensive menu and offers a large variety of set meals so no matter what your preference are, they've got you covered. The set meal here are affordable priced. Most of them come with Chawanmushi, Rice, Miso Soup and Sashimi. My chicken nanban set come with tempura soft shell crab üòã The tartar sauce goes very well with chicken and salmon is thickly sliced and fresh. Chawanmushi was just normal.

Ig: @zoey_belle_

Don't let it's humble shopfront fool you. The food is nothing less than legendary. My elder brother stays nearby for years and I have passed this store countless times. Strangely on the eve of his relocation, he suggested to dine here and he has never been here before. It was a last minute reservation (made 30mins before we arrive) and it looks a little empty for a saturday night.

Honestly I didnt harbour much expectations and ordered mainly the signature items which are less likely to go wrong. The dishes were promptly served and oh boy.. i was so wrong. The chicken soup is flavourful and though most of us didnt like chinese parsley and there was abundance in it, we slurped our bowls empty in no time (skipping the parsley of course) and found ourselves wanting more! The assam fish we've had before were mostly a tad too sour and this was amazingly balanced, the fish was cooked just right. Despite swearing to go on a diet, i had to have half a portion of rice to go with the sauce or I will sleep with regrets.

The final dish that came which sealed the deal was the signature prawn noodle. Gu ma jia is located just steps away from a famous prawn noodle available in single portions at a starting price of $5 while for this, the only size comes in a huge claypot at $30 but I will gladly choose this in a heartbeat. The broth is rich and yummy of course but what's shocking is there is wokhey. Show of hands, who had prawn noodles that had wokhey?

The other dishes that I didnt mention does not mean it wasnt crazy good. I just didnt wanna give any more spoilers. Go explore places that may not seem instaworthy, for a change, and they might surprise you with a dinner that you will remember for life.
Wonderful place for birthday lunch. Had buffet lunch there, food and service was great.

Ordered family set online and the food tasted terrible. Red Tom Yum seafood soup was so salty like a full jar of salt was added in. The salted fish fried rice was also too salty. Waste of money as the other dishes like pandan leaf chicken and honey chicken were also not well cooked as lacked flavour. A total waste of money as not palatable at all. If can give no star, I would want to do that. Please check your chef's cooking skill before serving the food to your customer.
Just an average eatery outlet, however unless you get a seat outdoor, inside is pretty warm to enjoy your meal in this present weather condition. It us a bit difficult to enjoy your food.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
1. Took my order wrongly
2. Portion is pathetic

Please improve ..

Service is acceptable. Food portion is quite big, however its just average. Do try the soft shell & mudcrab fried rice. Skip the cereal fish and chip and truffle fries. I was told that there is always complimentary dessert, but I didn't get it as the staff claims that they are running short of it. However was given complimentary chicken wing. Price is slight high $$$. But good thing is the service charge is included in cost of the dishes.

The food is good, the pork could be better.
Service is excellent and food were served very fast.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Excellent service. The spicy lamb is something to die for. Cooked just right with the right chewiness and spiciness.

Good food at affordable price. Decided to try this place after my treatment at the TCM next door. Overall the food is good and the service staff is friendly and efficient.  20% off meal course from 3 to 5pm

Their signature duck was extremely good, however the rest of the dishes were rather mediocre. The crab and fish maw soup had barely any crab meat in it; it was probably too finely shredded you couldn‚Äôt see or even taste it. We had to add lots of vinegar into the soup else it‚Äôll be bland.

The sauce of the barramundi went well with it, ensuring there wasn‚Äôt a fishy smell or taste to it.

The decor inside is really nicely set up, with dimmed lights to make the ambience cosy and intimate. Ladies, it can get quite chilly.

For the kind of price you pay here, you can easily get better quality Chinese cuisine elsewhere. It was a nice experience nevertheless!
The service is poor. The person who served with the name ‚ÄúTL‚Äù is very impolite.

restaurant name: Kow Loon Hong Kong Dim Sum
content:
Food is not so nice. The guo tie wrapper was thick and the filling was dry. The egg tart custard was jiggly and tasty, but the pasty was somewhat soggy. The rice rolls were so thick, it was like eating chunks of steamed rice flour. The steamed chicken feet were good though.
This stall should indicate their prices clearly, either on the display or on the menu. We only got to find out the prices at the point of ordering.
seriously the best thai food in singapore. so satisfying and affordable! better than anything ive tried in singapore. the lady is extremely friendly too. have been coming here for over 6 years!
Consistently the best nasi lemak and mee goreng in Taman Jurong! And I'm comparing this to Latiffa Huri at Jurong West!

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
I am a local staying near the toapayoh store. Ordered 2 items at 6.30pm and only got my food at 7.10pm. 40minutes wait
Bad attitude no apology, still can stare at me

Latest Malaysia hawker food themed restaurant in Singapore. Lots to choose from and stalls display famous roads to state  exactly where the dishes come from. I wonder if this is really the case. Prices are not cheap. It‚Äôs like paying premium for the name and air con. Char kway teow could pass off as Penang char kway teow but lacked hum and lup cheong. Penang laksa was chock full of vegetables. Quite close to the real thing although I probably didn‚Äôt try this style before. Chendol had the right taste but ice shavings were not fine enough.
Great tasting ramen. Quality of the soup and noodles are made to excellent.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content:
I have been visiting this place for a long time and regularly as I work in Vision Exchange building. But sadly The quality of food is going down day by day.

Today I ordered mutton biryani - it came with a large piece of mutton but extremely tough. Couldn't chew it. So had to throw away mutton.

Basically I just got then 1 egg and biryani rice for the price of mutton biryani.
Always loving it! First time I had the satay! The chicken is so tender and soft!!

First time trying, ordered take away - the special of the day, Mutton Dum Briyani, cauliflower and papadom. Paid SGD21.60. Busy during weekend lunch time but was served shortly. They also have the counter which is like the mixed rice concept. Q to be served to chose the dish and food. The food still smell good after 15 mins when i reached home. The overall portion is huge however the mutton portion inside is not alot, the rice is alot. Rice is fragrance and tasty. Mutton is tender. Worth a try.

This is japanese cuisine (inside poiz center). My favorite is champion floss maki and chuka hotate. Tastes wise is normal, salmon hana maki is fresh, and the sushi is just nice. The wasabi is not fresh i think..Related the price i consider in the middle range. Average price roughly 16sgd(for 8 pcs sushi) and 7-8sgd for 4pcs and similiar price with udon. All menu has small or large portion, and of course the price will be different. Those that really want to have quick grab, you can come into this place and just order don menu ya. FYI, their portion is quite generous as overall..

Average food, terrible service. There weren't many customers at the time my family went, but the guy behind the cashier seemed too busy to want to take our orders/queries. The guy clearing up the table was also inconsiderate as he wanted to clear my half-finished food TWICE. Absolutely grumpy staff.

Tried the Dim Sum and overall good experience. The pan fried Carrot Cake has good sear on it for favour and taste. The Salted Egg Lava Bun was so-so, didn't have that good oozing of the salted egg lava.

Nice place to bring kids along.  Sushi is nice, affordable prices.
AI leading to our seats, interesting for kids.

Came here for a nice, quiet dinner on a Tuesday evening during school term. A quiet respite that lifts you away from the hustle and bustle of university life. Food was great - ordered the tender beef cheeks cooked to perfection and the crabmeat pasta fully infused with the flavour of crab. Menu is on the pricier side ($18-$30 for mains) excl. service charge and GST but the quality of food is great. Would definitely visit again!

Tried this famous prawn noodle stall last weekend. The broth was really good, rich and not too overpowering. The highlight I would say is the chilli. Gave a good kick for me! The prawns were fresh too, but 2 seems a bit little, an extra one would be better! :)

dude i love this place so much. i‚Äôm a student currently and it‚Äôs one of the most affordable and best tasting ramen for its price. meat is fresh and cut on site, noodles are springy oso. the guy running the stall is a real g as well. 10/10 recomment

The Famous Fried Rice I ordered was one of the best I've ever eaten. However, nothing else really caught my attention, but do keep in mind that I am a very fussy eater. The rest of the table agreed that the food was amazing and they also praised it for its generous portion and cheaper price.

If you plan to eat dinner here, either make a reservation or come extra-early or you will not manage to get a table. Nearly every large table had a "Reserved" sign on it when I walked in.

The parking spots right outside get filled up fast, and the closest alternative (slight farther down the street, behind the restaurant) costs 60 cents per hour. There is a valet outside the restaurant that will gladly help.

First time trying out this outlet in Djitsun Mall. The one at Kovan was fine.
Must compliment the staff for fast and good service even it was a Sunday evening. Food was good and not too expensive.
We had 2 combo meals and pizza for only about $53 including tax.
Will definitely come again for meals soon.
$$$ food wise nothing special.
Nice penang prawn noodle, teh o peng in retro metal mug & traditional apam snacks

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content:
I was very disappointed with my visit today which was a stark difference from my last visit a few years back.

The single and most important part of chicken rice has got to be the rice. What we got was a plate of undercooked rice that was bland as well. The roast chicken wasn't any better as the meat tasted dry and overcooked.

The Kang Kong and hot plate tofu were decent and the saving grace of our dinner was probably the prawn roll. Service standards didn't do them a favour either. Don't think I'll be back here anytime soon.

Brought customer for lunch yesterday, 3 of us rejected by the stuff here..
The stuff: Show me your address
I said: We are not living in the same address ‚Ä¶
A beer house with Japanese food menu and quite a few selections of draft beer, wine and liquor. Good indoor ambience with a few outdoor tables. Great for couples or small groups.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Majority of store can‚Äôt even understand English. Gets my order wrong 70% of the time. Good food but if they constantly make us pay for the wrong orders then what‚Äôs the point.
Food is delicious and staff is very friendly. Definitely one of my to-go restaurant.

Ordered 3 pieces of Prata and had to wait almost 30mins. The queue is not long. Place not crowded. Workers too slow.
Avoid the place.
A good variety of food - Chinese, Korean, India, etc etc, and the food is nice.

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Conveniently located inside TPY Safra. Staff are extremely friendly and polite, able to notice any needs you have before you even ask for it. Drinks are refilled proactively before they are empty. Food tastes really good, Sweet Basil Chicken and Red Tomyum are really worth trying, highly recommended place.

The prata made were tough to bite but the gravy was of top quality. There were few people to clear the empty dishes at the counter when we returned them. It was messy. The washing basin cubicle is too small and people with broader shoulder could not reach in to wash hands. There was a poor man inside the restaurant harassing people to offer free food or money. The counter staff were fully aware but chose not to see.

We tried their Rib Eye Steak (medium doneness) with Black Pepper sauce and Hickory Smoked BBQ Pork Rib from their many items for lunch. Serving sizes were big and waiting time was around 10 minutes. Crispy curly fries were really nice. We had different views on the corns and coleslaw. Meats could easily be torn apart. Only thing was that pork rib sauce was a bit too salty.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Really tasty and the waiting time was 7 mins for a succulent chicken thigh. Worth the wait. Thanks for the great lunch!

Being here for some many times. So I have to review again after last visit. The roasted duck is horrible. definitely not fresh, it come with a strong ransid and a stale meat taste. service standard drops alot as well.
Pretty decent Chinese cuisine. Quiet and classy ambience.
Ambience and the Dishes are still same‚Ä¶ good!

Must try it yourself. Come early to avoid the crowd. Easy parking. If you love smoky favours of meat then this is the place you must visit. The soup and mashed potatoes by chef Kelvin is to die for. Also do call to check availability for their weekly flown in oysters from france. BTW the kopitiam also has draft üç∫ and delicious thai food too.

Tasted mee rebus from this stall, probably one of the best in Singapore, stall is clean, food is nicely prepared and presented, price is reasonable too. üëç, I can‚Äôt wait to come back again and try other food from Seri !
Food is SUPERB! Love the quality of food here! Service is excellent! Will definitely come back again!

Great service staff and the food is affordable and tasty. I come here often for my meal. It could be quite pack during the weekend. I order the daily set meal which I find it very tasty. The unagi fish very done perfectly. The prawn roll was nicely done too. The potato salad was crisp in taste. The mini octupus was not quite good though. It comes in big size which does not match the tiny name given. Overall I still love this restaurant.
