Great Service and very reasonably priced dishes. Their fish promotion fish is superb!

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
Great place for chilling with friends and good mookata üòãüòãüòã Good quality beef & meat, even the butter is special!! No thristy feel after meal *burp burp*.
They serve variety of good beer, sweet fresh coconut and drinks too!
Tables are well spaced apart, toilets is very clean, they have handwash available ard e dinning area so need not go all the way to toilet. Totally value up!

I found the meal to be satisfactory, and their potato with sour cream to be delicious as usual. The restaurant was crowded during lunch, but I found the staff to be attentive and responsive.

Perhaps a downside is that the soup was a bit plain, but no major complaints other than that.

My favorite sushi goes to a place. They have a variety of choices, and the sushi is made fresh based on orders. The only problem is they only served one small plate of sauce (wasabi and soy sauce per person) when you are seated. You need to request more soy sauce when you finish it.

Eating area is dirty and utensils not clean properly. Not sure if any inspection done for this outlet. The lady staff seems hostile and made no effort to apologise for being late in delivery service. Poor attitude. I ended up asking for a refund for some of my order.

No quality and expensive.. $7 for a plate of so called ‚Äúseafood‚Äù hor fun with only 1 not fresh small prawn and few pieces of sotong at a void deck Coffeeshop..  when we double check with the menu it was only written as $6 and they even argue because I ask for seafood? Hmmm... better watch it when you do decide to come here to eat..

Visited with my family for the 1st time on a weekend.
Thoroughly enjoyed the food here, considering the price point the quality is really comparable to restaurants.
The gyoza is really the main star here, perfect meat to skin ratio.
Karage fried to perfection
For the tonkotsu broth, I find that it could be even more creamier.
The choice of ramen noodles wasn't what I expected. A thicker noodle would better complement the broth in my opinion.
Otherwise, really hope this place keeps being consistent in the standard of the food.
Came for afternoon dimsum buffet. Self serve certain items while order ala carte for the rest. Time limit of 90 minutes per table
Food is good. Service is fast.

Tasted the cheese prata with teh halia Ice. Superb nicely tasting food. Only reason I'm not giving 5 star cause I thought it's halal but they sell alcohol so by the time I realise too late. So Muslim friends just take note ya. Unless u don't mind the food is great.
Great service and the staff were very very good and accommodating to our request. Highly recommanded especially chun rong she was very very good.
The staff is very unhelpful , unfriendly and impatient just wanted to ask very extra gravy and said no for better dining experience dine at red ginger at imm

It's cheap, have nice decor n aircon. Yam cake is good enough. Laksa n special chee cheong fun is not so good, try ordering other stuff. Can improve by tidying n decor the place better. Service can be faster. Prices should be clearly stated. Go during off peak to find a seat. I will still give 5 star because it's cheap n unique place.

Those good food is good delicious but need to really take good care on how to store RAW food meats and seafood outside for long hours.  This can cause food poisoning if all the RAW food ingredient place outside for so long.  Hope management really take care this serious issue

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Was doubting the name of ‚Äúbest Indian food‚Äù and came here to try. But it surprised me with its flavors. Ordered a set of North Indian Thalli and one special Thalli. It came with 5+ different curries with bread and rice. From savory to sweet curry are all really amazing. Def worth a try!

Surprised by the crowd at this quaint coffeeshop. Went on a weekday and the crowd started to pile in after 7pm.
Ordered a platter consisting of beef brisket, chicken and pork belly which comes with two sides. It was awesome! Perfect for a mini get together of 3 or even 4 if u order another side or something.
I loved the smoked beef briskets, plenty of fats in this one tho. Not for the faint of heart. The bbq chicken has a good flavour, well grilled I will say.
Pork belly was a bit on the dry side but I enjoyed the flavour it had.
We had two sides, the ratatouille and the garlic fries. The fries wasn‚Äôt too overpowering, with the garlic taste just showing through enough. Having the ratatouille with the meats balanced off the meal.
In all I‚Äôll say it‚Äôs good food that should go into a good gathering. Oh the Coffeeshop serves Archipelago brews too!

We got the buffet. The food was cold and tough. Service was appalling-  first time seeing a manager who shout back at a customer. Staff only able to speak Mandarin.
My suggestion is to go somewhere else.
If you‚Äôre craving for some really good nasi lemak, come down to this place. Well worth the $4.50
Excellent noodles which were not too springy or too soft. We had a great server, Lisa - she took the time to understand what we liked and was attentive and checked if we needed more tea.
Tried their 4 pax menu and we were decently full! The lor mee is comparable to many other places I‚Äôve tried and the fish was tasty. Never tried fried yam before but I think they made it quite well.
I love the food in this place. Cheap, portion is just nice and really decent quality (btr than sakae sushi imo) for the price.

I don‚Äôt know I eat mee kuah or mee kuah bubble like going to rotten. I don‚Äôt know how long they keep the gravy. Seriously your food much more better at Sembawang not over here. Can you go find new chef to cook!!! Very bad service ever. Last time I buy nasi goreng ayam, not even 3 hours then cannot eat already.. Please check your staff lah.

Today 11/04/2022

My hubby bought roti john. But this roti john only egg & onion. And not fully ya.. Please if u can‚Äôt serve properly to customers, please close down your lousy biz. Food is not cheap nowadays.. And yes we have to eat even though your service really bad.

I came here over few occasions always ordered their signature dishes. This time just pick few dishes from the menu. All turn out good if not better than other restaurants. The fried baby squid is one of the better one. Ordered a deep fried sea bass HK style. We thought is $28/kg but it was $28 for the fish. Good value.

Rude middle aged woman manning the store. Prepared the order for eat-in even though she asked twice and I‚Äôve confirmed both times that it‚Äôs for takeaway. When I received my order and told her it‚Äôs for takeaway, she started scolding me, and told the kitchen folks that I ‚Äúchanged my mind again‚Äù.

She said, ‚Äúif it‚Äôs really for takeaway, why did you accept my order pager?‚Äù

It was my first time at that store. Who would know that a pager is only meant for eat in?

Food wasn‚Äôt even good. Not recommended.

Amazing Chinese food that's elevated. Great ambience, awesome service, and surprisingly good value. If you want good Chinese food but don't want to eat the same old jumbo and actually want to have good atmosphere and a modern twist, this is a great place.

Do not ever book a wedding banquet with this restaurant. I booked a wedding banquet on November 2019 for my wedding to be held at Singapore Chinese Cultural Centre (SCCC) on December 2020. Due to the covid-19 situation, SCCC had refunded me the booking deposit for the venue. However, Gim Tim (the caterer) abide by their ‚Äúnon-refundable‚Äù deposit and forced us to use the deposit to invite our guests for a meal at their premises under a HDB void deck. As a wedding is a once in a lifetime event, and Gim Tim was reluctant to refund us with our deposit, we were forced to get our guests to their premises at Ang Mo Kio. I had since then swear on telling everyone I know of to not patron Gim Tim. My family and extended family will never ever visit or dine at Gim Tim ever again. Please think twice before you spend money in this restaurant. There are so many restaurants in Singapore and will you ever want to help a restaurant who behaves and acts in such a manner in difficult times?

restaurant name: NEW KORAT MOOKATA - 711 Ang Mo Kio Central
content: portion is just nice , pricing is reasonable, will definitely come back again !!!

Atas chicken rice;

generous portions.

Food is really good but unfortunately, the service provided in this restaurant at Northpoint was subpar. Grill cod fish was served cold, with diluted/watery teriyaki sauce. Service staff was almost non-existent. Sushi took about 35 minutes to serve. This was after I politely reminded the staff that I still have missing orders.

Came to this restaurant to celebrate a birthday. The Cantonese food was very good, I was actually very surprised by the flavor of the Beijing duck skin which was very fragrant. The service of the staff who was serving us was excellent, despite being super busy that day with lots of customers!

restaurant name: Golden Spoon Eating House and Catering
content:
There many names for this canteen but this is probably the only canteen that is open till late 11pm is the closing time for its last store, economic bee hoon. Not for picky eaters, it fulfil the purpose of a supper and the staff is pretty friendly.

Would like to give a shout out to a hidden gem. There's a Thai wester fusion store here and the green curry is pretty not bad. A 3.5-4/5 mark I would give, the flavouring is there and the spiciness mild yet with existence.

This is still a review in doing as I try more food but haha more await

Wouldn‚Äôt recommend their side dishes at all.  Tandoori chicken and butter chicken were so dry that you can barely chew the chunks of meat. Saving grace was probably just the gravy from the butter chicken.

One of the best midnight food haunts within Yishun.

Offers plenty of our local Indian food options, prata, murtabaks, mee gorengs and what nots.

Price wise, definitely more worth than its competitors within the area.

Parking space are never a hassle. Plenty of available lots.
The curry chicken is good, poured gravy over the rice, making it very flavourful. Have not tried the part yet. Good service as the staff kept walking around asking if the food is ok.
Nice ambience with alot to offer than known. Rustic dated back to old SG shophouses. Staffs are pleasant
Nice environment, the ambience is very welcoming. Amazing food and service. Highly recommended.
Extremely slow.

I got my order in less than 3mins which is very fast. They had about 4 or 5 workers around which probably explains the cost of the food..
It's mostly the only place in NTU open to eat till midnight and they use that as a leverage to serve NON-FRESH food, mostly buns. On a good side, staff is very nice.

The food was normal not as what I expected. Serving of food is quite stingy amid the high prices. Ambience is just like at a hawker ctr but little better becos it's lightly airconned. Staff may be a little conservatively reserved,a smile could make us feel more welcomed. May skip this place for another visit.

I wish I could leave a pic here too... just now got the order via Food panda.  And the size of fried "large" hor fun is simply outrageous! Dined here twice. Subsequently tried to revisit on 2 occasions, but the staff were either missing (smoking outside the condo perimeter) or ignored 2 customers standing by the door.

This new vegetarian salad place in NTU, Singapore is great. You can chose a regular or large size salad. They have pasta, rice or potatoes to choose for carbs which is good cos one doesn't get bored of taking same carb. I recommend their cheesy pumpkins. The creamy eggs cost extra but it is quite tasty. The staff are nice too. Over all affordable and to go place to eat in NTU.
Nice place for Sushi

Claypot Bah Kut Teh: The soup was bland and tasteless. One could be deceived by the colour of the soup which gave the impression that it was briming with taste. There was a grand total of 2 to 3 small chucks of pork and a maximum of 3 thinly sliced pork belly. Portion was small. $6 for that tiny serving and $1 more if you want a bowl of rice. Tasteless, tiny serving and a long wait for your food.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: This was the menu at the Marina Square location that we went to. It all looked SO TASTY when we went to visit back in January 2020 but I couldn‚Äôt taste any of the food being so sick on that trip. Can‚Äôt wait to come back and give this place a try!

Made a reservation here and specially travelled here from the east. However, my dad forgot to bring his phone but only his token. The waiter refused to allow to enter since my dad do not have his phone.

I asked them to used the app to perform the verification but they refused to do so. Very disappointed by their service. They are probably sticking to traditions...

If you wish to come pls remember to bring your phone and ur old parents' phones too.

The so called famous chicken is average tasting to me. I guess the wow factor for most pple was the flames. The zichar stall serves decent food.

Beer bundle deals are good. Great place to gather with friends.
We know how it's always feel wonderful to be back to where we belong..  Your alma mater.. To see how much has changed over the last twenty years is just amazing..

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content:
A relaxing place for chinese food., Dishes are beautifully balance in taste. Refreshing pickles/fermented
plum n salty vegetables in steam fish/ chicken, a grade above. But expect to spend a bit above the average resturant prices

The is a small restaurant, hence sitting is limited. Be prepare to share table if it gets too crowded. The food is good and price is reasonable. The lor mee, fried sliced fish and oyster omelette are good. I find the fried bee Hoon too dry to my liking although the bee Hoon is fried until so fluffy. We enjoyed our meal.

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: The Thai Sea Bass was tastefully done, so does the mookata. But room for improvement is that they could ensure the fire of the Sea Bass and mookata was bigger, because the soup and gravy did not boiled at all...

One of the best Indian muslim food restaurants in Chong Pang! Indian rojak, mutton/chicken steaks, their masala dosa's red chilli chutney is super nice better than some that I have eaten previously, they also make nice drinks too eg. Teh O limau panas just nice not too thick and not super sweet and their Milo kosong is well done with just the exact amount of Milo powder portion!
great price and awesome teh halia (order less sweet)
Nice steak. Ordered as the stall open at 5pm, then get my order at 5:30pm. Luckily the food worth the waiting time

This is the first time im taking photo of my delivered food.

Ordered via foopanda for lunch. I could smell the food as soon as I opened my door. Food was still very hot and very well packed. Tom yum was wrapped and no spillage.

Food was tasty and perfectly spicy as I asked for extra chili. They also gave chili at the side. 2 large prawns in the soup. Perfectly frid egg. It is worth it for delivery of hawker food. Thank you for cooking.

The cold crab is ok but the rest is not nice. I had lowered my standard but still fail beyond commercial standard.The teochew fried kway teow, oyster omelet n especially the  signature pomfret is totally disappointed. Poor taste. I think my wife, a housewife can cook very much better. Dun understand such a popular teochew restaurant provide such low standard. Too surprise to me liao. How to go back?

All time favourite. Located at the 2nd level of AMK hub.

Fast and good service.

Love the food but it lacked pork katsu.

Service staff are friendly.

This is a small humble stand alone restaurant under the void decks of a HDB flat. There are hardly more than 8 tables in there and do be sure to call and make a reservation before heading down. They are almost certain to be fully packed everytime i go over without a reservation. They serve really solid la mian, xiao long baos and sheng jian baos (favourite). For a small restaurant, i think the items in the menu is just sufficient for them to run the store efficiently without giving much choices to diners.

in my opinion, i love the XLBs here more than other stores. Only issue with the XLB here is that the skin have not achieve the standard of DTF type. But i feel that the meat and soup within is better than DTF which makes it a must visit place for me. The sheng jian bao here is well done, not oily and the stuffing is very season and marinated.

Definitely will be back to visit.

Been here a couple of times, round tables with cushion seat is quite squeezy for 7 adults + 2 kids, do request for non-cushioned seats for large group.

Lor Mee was fantastic as usual, standard is always the same. Must orders are the Braised Pig Intestines, Sweet & Sour Pork with Lychee, Stir Fried Yam.

Kids always have a set meal for them, usually either fried rice or porridge.

Desserts are veryyyy mehhhhh, can skip on this.
Chong fan yummy. Curry mee was great except the chicken meat (got a "frozen" smell which was not so nice when consumed)

THE WORST PLACE TO GO. The food isn‚Äôt fresh and they‚Äôre service is poorly Match and I don‚Äôt understand what they are trying to do. If you wanna try good food and good service never ever come to this store, period.

We ordered delivery since heightened alert in May. Made several rounds of changes to reservations due to restrictions. Lady was super patient in handling changes including menu change. I was quite paiseh. She eventually delivered it to me personally to Punggol in Sept. On time. Food was good. The $99 crab promo for 2 was worth it. Surprisingly not small for the price. Lala n tofu were good too. Hopefully to visit the actual store soon.

We would like to think that the waiter discreetly warned us a couple of times subtly over selection not being wise. 1- repeating and reconfirming a meal selection/add on a couple of times, 2- end up not serving the add-on(paid $2), 3-we even asked for the add on and then it was served. Moral of the story: listen to subtle signs there.
Overall it was okay, approximately $170 for six of us, inclusive of drink and soup or dessert; there was a set meal option available to all main courses with an addition of 6.50-drinks were already close to that price.

Need to wait 10-20mins for the buzzer to ring after making order. Always many people order from here. Good business. Somehow the plate is bigger than whats being served. Anyway i like their grilled fish, so give them 4 stars.
The prata taste nice, non oily and crispy.Their Thosai also yummyüëç

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content:
We've been patronising Crystal Jade since they started and through the years they have expanded and grew more outlets.

Different outlet's chefs perform differently hence we have favourite outlets. Our first choice used to be at Holland Village. Another favourite haunt is the one at Ngee Ann City.

Recently, we've been ordering from their Toa Payoh outlet for home delivery. Although the experience is not as good as in-house dining, the convenience and quality of the takeout more than makes up for it.

My grandchildren love their beef so we usually order 2 portions. Another favourite dish we would order in twos is the four season beans. The lion head meatball stew is delicious but I prefer a more meaty bite. I find them a little mushy for my taste but perhaps the young children and older folks may like it that way. The tofu stew is also very delicious. I appreciate that they pack the sweet and sour fish sauce separately from the fried fish. Overall, we are happy with our delivered meals and will continue to order from this outlet.
The broth wasn't tasty and the clams were tasteless. The staff was dancing around with the songs blasting didn't give me a good dining experience.

(Translated by Google) The first time I gave the evaluation because I have never had a meal and I feel sad... I like to eat garlic water spinach, but I didn‚Äôt expect it to be made like this. All are leaves and the stems are small. Obviously the dishes are not fresh... Garlic... Mapo tofu feels like boiled tofu with bean paste... It doesn't have any spiciness... I'm disappointed that it should not come... I hope the store can treat consumers more sincerely. I have a few comments, I hope it can be improved.

Nice foods and good service

Been coming here since young, food still tastes good, potato in a jacket still tastes as good as before. My parents still hold fond memories of this place - the deco (which includes the Christmas mugs they use for their Christmas lunches)

Food service was a little slow in my recent visit.

However, food portion did get smaller. Dad ordered the chicken and mum ordered the chicken and fish (for a dollar more). Dad‚Äôs chicken portion was actually smaller than mum‚Äôs.

TLDR: food is still great, food portion got smaller and perhaps pricier too.

Food is ok. Prefer the outlet at West Coast (permanently closed) where staff were friendly and the food was better. The water melon juice was diluted. Maybe too much ice. Will try other outlet next time.
The meat is huge, and the food is great tasting too..price is affordable as its a cafe in hdb estates
Very nice üëå

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Dissappointing food. Bought 2 crabs, 1 chilli and 1 pepper. Both were adequate. Tasted worse than what you find at some other coffee shops. The food here was not worthy of a celebrity chef's reputation. The only reason i gave 2 stars is because of the great service from the waitresses and the view.

Very satisfying meal. Not disappointed after multiple visits. Always up to expectation. Very good to satisfy cravings for Thai food in the neighbourhood.

Highly recommend crispy papaya salad which elevates the usual papaya salad into something fun and indulgent, not usually found on menus. Great as a starter and adds a lot of crunch texture to your meal. Also recommend Tofu hot plate which comes with egg tofu, egg and some meat and seafood with comes sizzling hot. Great with rice.
Standard basil pork/chicken always consistent. Tom Saap hits all the spot for spicy Tom yum craving. Great balance or sourness and savouriness.

Love to end with my favourite red Ruby dessert. They usually serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream for added creaminess.

For prata fix, anytime!

Personally prefer the egg or onion version as its prepared thin, crispy and long. vs the plain prata which is made thick and round.

Drinks are always too sweet, so I would ask for less sweet. Healthy living is the way to go.

Wasn't too crowded on a Friday evening.

Friendly service. Truffle beef don taste is on point and at a decent price. Looks like it's quite popular during lunch hours so come early unless you are ok with a slight wait.

Pro tip: buy the $50 favepay coupon for $40. Works perfectly and you get 4mpd if you double up and load up crv as payment method in fave.

A typical nasi lemak at Whampoa. The queue is Long, cause of its pricing(pretty affordable). I‚Äôm a fan of nasi lemak and I must say this is just an average nasi lemak. The rice can be better(slightly mushy when I ate it) but it‚Äôs side dishes are good.

Love the traditional variety type of Chinese food here. The roast duck and chicken were crispy and well done as usual. The cold combination dish was great too! The sliced garoupa fish dish turned out fresh and flavourful, the way I love it! My fave must be the braised tofu with tau kee as it was superbly done with broth that was not too starchy, just right and really tasty!

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Loved the food and service

The Service is fantastic, the food is awesome üôèüèºüëç
Will come again üòâ

Very tasty quality food!! Had the bee hoon goreng & quick to served. Bee hoon is soft & fluffy easy to digest. Cook in high heat & Still hot even half way eating, highly recommended!! Not much oil used to cook the dish compare to other Indian restaurants usually very oily is a great encouragement for the revisit. Price is a bit high with plain bee hoon with egg only at $4, but is worth for eating a delicious food in air cond place. So glad i never stir the Hot lime tea as a lot of sugar at the bottom. Hopefully they can offer more vegetarian dish.

An extremely satisfying dinner. The BBQ chicken is simply awesome...you can taste the smoke, as you bite into its tender and juicy meat.

As recommended by so many other reviewers, the whipped potato is really a must to try!

If there is a 6 star rating, I'll definately give 6 stars‚≠ê
Stroll Through A Few Rounds & Finally Decided To Settle Down Here For Lunch w Some Expectations Of Coz~ However, Service Disappointing, Food Disappointing!!üòîüòîüòî

Cosy and authentic Thai food at very reasonable prices! Each dish costs on average $6. The prawn cake was hot and crispy, tomyam soup was spicy and sour enough, green curry super creamy and egg fluffy and stuffed with prawns. This will be our new Thai go to restaurant in SG...
Very good portions and very healthy! I order via Grabfood so don‚Äôt know what the store front is like. The seafood is fresh and tasty, a good option if need a nice and healthy meal

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
One of the best Korean restaurant in Singapore! The spicy seafood noodle soup (jjambong) and black bean paste noodle (jjajang myeon) is great. The noodle itself is chewy, taste as great as freshly handmade noodle! The jjambong soup is so flavourful, it just make me crave for more even I'm a person who can't really takes spicy food.

The tangsuyok also taste great. You can tell the greatness just by the smell of the fried pork! With the layer of sweet and sour source, it's just heavenly!

Definitely coming back for more!

Queue is arnd 4hrs, went during $1 promo, started queuing at 1030. Started eating at 1430

Staff were friendly and helped us made our 3 tower stacks

Sashimi is 4/5 due to not being as cold as I'd expect. Nonetheless, great experience there

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Went as recommended by my Korean colleague for Jjajangmyeon. First taste on Jjajangmyeon is not too smoky like OBBA or sweet like Mukjia. Noodles is in between Itaewon‚Äôs and OBBA. Find that smaller size onions taste better but here is bigger slice. The minced pork here is bigger in size and not so dry as compared to the other restaurants mentioned above. The sauce here is most watery of the 4.
For the fried dumplings, I must recommend. The skin is akin to biscuit taste n the fillings is good.

Relatively long wait for the food on a Sunday morning. The place is in high demand from walk-ins and delivery takeouts. Had the murtaburger, which was very tasty and filling. Prices are higher than your average prata place.

Comfy seats, nice ambience at almost every outlet. Sushi tei is the go to jap restaurant for a quick fix to your Japanese È£ü„ÅπÁâ©cravings. Food quality is almost consistent and quite fresh. Firm favs remain the mentaiko salmon, sashimi salad, ‚Ä¶
Ordered peking duck and chilli crab for delivery. Both taste good. Crab very fresh, full of meat. Must try. Free delivery charge for order above 80.
3pm to 5pm lunch break
Served by Auntie Peggy, friendly staff. Free additional ramen per order, i finished all as it is yummy. Affordable price.

The food is better than most thai restaurant in Singapore. Was very surprise their north eastern thai dishes (larb moo) is very close to what you would have in thailand.

Fried pork was slightly hard, and the marinade was hardly present. Fish cake was so-so.

Their stuff chicken Wings was rather good though. Crispy on the outside, tasty on the inside.

Food is only slightly more expensive as compare to most thaifood places. Golden Mile Seems to charge a premium for it.

Overall every good Experience, will still return.

I have to say it‚Äôs priced on the high side for a central hub hdb area. But the noodle was just very well done with just the right amount of seasoning and the roast duck leg was excellent.  I‚Äôve paid much much more for worst food at Holland village. I read many comments about price verus quantity.  I rather eat high quality then quantity.  It doesn‚Äôt get 5 stars because $9 for my noodle priced out a lot of older uncles and aunties.

This Swatow restaurant is located at 181 Toa Payoh #02-602,  Lorong 4, Singapore 310181.

This restaurant is quite spacious in all but not cooling enough.

We went for weekend buffet.  The restaurant was almost fully occupied; partly as being a Saturday, secondly there will be no dine-in from Sunday onwards.

The food were served very quickly by  push-carts crews.  There were quite a variety of food to opt for.  We did not take up some of the food offered in order not to waste.

The chicken feets if cooked in a little spicy way will be best.
The food and desserts were fine so far.

A surprise find along Neil Road is Jing Hua Xiao Chi. After the huge disappointment previously at the nearby Maxwell Hawker Centre for Wo Tie (Pot Stickers), a find just 5 mins walk away managed to wash away that disappointment.

Opened in 1989, this local homegrown restaurant specialises in traditional Chinese Dumplings and other Chinese Appetisers. All the dishes and Dumplings are handmade and not factory prepared. Decided to order some takeaway food to sample their dishes.

The Pan-Fried Mixed Seafood & Pork Dumplings were exquisite. The skin was pan-fried and seared to have a light crunch while keeping the juices of the meat within. When paired with the vinegar and ginger strips, it was so good.

The other item ordered was the Chinese Pizza. Yes, the name is somewhat misleading. It is like a cross between a Pastry Pie and the Pork Dumplings. It was an interesting dish and just as enjoyable as the Pork Dumplings.

From the above, this restaurant is definitely a go to place for future cravings of Wo Tie (Pot Stickers).

General Verdict: Traditional Chinese Appetisers done well and done properly for a wonderful gastronomical experience

Opening Hours: Daily 11:30am-3pm and 5:30pm-9:30pm

Queue Situation: Next to none but seats within are generally filled

Price: SG$8.50 upwards

Value for money place. I come here every weekend cos all the Tuition Centre‚Äôs are here thus a convenient place for a meal.

Nice ambience for about $15 per pax for lunch.

The grilled fish with Tom Yum sauce was our favorite but unfortunately they took it off the menu as it was a temporary promotion.

The current promotion of lamb chops aren‚Äôt that great. Too thinly sliced and tough..

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: After waiting for over 2 years due to Covid-19 to dine-in, the dishes are delicious, service is superb as always.

A Japanese style cafe with 10 tables in the Venue. It is 2 bus stops away from Potong Pasir MRT. Family friendly. It serves A5 Wagyu Beef, Aburi Salmon Don, Ichiraku Ramen, Tori Katsu, Tonkatsu, sake, Sapporo draft beers by tap, and other finger foods.

Not a great value preposition at $1 per stick of very cheap ingredient. But you can't beat the good variety of fried veggies, meat and seafood to accompany your mookata (23 in all). Although there is a minor queue when I turned up, the food is served fast (within 10 mins). You can choose from a selection of 4 sauces (satay, sweet thai chili,  sweet sauce and  homemade made Chilli). The place was rocking when I turned up (around 7.45pm) on Friday. The place attracts the young crowd and I recommend the outer sitting areas ( which is cooler). The place can get quite warm because of the many platters of mookata sizzling. I have chosen the mushroom set paired with a few odds and ends. The tare sauce with a dusting of white pepper on it enhances the nuances of fried unami. One thing can be improved is the rate of replenishment of the popular ingredients, the ingredients can be standby in the larger chiller in the back and quickly replenished in small batches as the night goes on. I happen to missed out on the eggplant üçÜ and fried fish because of that. But overall a good spot if you are looking for a platter of fried stuff and to nibble in a patpong soi vibe.

Tabao their ribeye steak. It‚Äôs tender and not gamey. Sauce is lightly peppered and not salty. I‚Äôm impressed with their fried potato ball. It‚Äôs crust is thin not oily and packed with flavour. Hope to have some garden veggies option than coleslaw.

Just realised I have been patronising this stall for 15 years ever since I was in secondary school and I think it really deserves a review. The food has been consistently good throughout the years and you get a good sense that the owners really take pride in their ingredients and quality.

I've also never had a dish here that disappointed me and when I visited today, the pork chop $7 was excellent, very tender and the portion generous. They also make their own coleslaw and this might be one of the best coleslaws I've tasted in Singapore (so none of that KFC garbage-tasting coleslaw). If you are looking for an affordable and filling meal, you can also pair their fried rice with a protein like chicken chop or fish.

So show some support for this little joint if you are in the area, you won't be disappointed!

Today having a very bad experience in this prata shop, one of the Chinese staff was shout at me from far. This was happened at timing 21:55.

What I was order come wrongly, but still shout at me. What kind of service attitude? Shop have CCTV recorded.
The best nasi lemak.....no issue parking also.

The signature sio bak was good, being crispy and a little chewy with a good lean to fat ratio.  At $15, it was a little on the pricey side.

We also liked the chai poh Teochew hor fun, which had wok hei.  The manageress recommended we try the steamed scallop dumplings with roe, but we found them on the fishy side, similar to the siew mai.

The fried radish cakes were okay, but the egg tarts were good.

Ambience and service were okay.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: My expectation of celebrity chef restaurant was kind of disappointing. The food is below average and you probably can get a better food quality at zhi Char place outside. Ordered their signature being first time here: chicken with fire: ‚Ä¶
The presentation of the delivery is terrible. Come on, $18 for the sushi, can you all get a properly sized container? And no ginger?

Pet-friendly place. I wouldn‚Äôt say it‚Äôs fantastic or novel but I tried it because of the good reviews. The otah bruschetta was thin and laid on top of a slice white bread. It‚Äôs quite hard to cut and dry. In terms of spiciness and taste, I‚Äôll rate it 2/5. In the end, i grab it with my hands and eat it. I don‚Äôt think it‚Äôll order it again because it‚Äôs not worth $18 (add $2 for cheese topping). Coffee is so-so ($7 up)

Great char-broiled meats at such reasonable prices! I've been there a couple of times and their meats are always so nicely charred, flavourful yet tender. Took away their Mad Spiced Chicken($7.90) on an astonishing bed of shredded cabbage with sesame sauce and a Pork Belly with Ratatouille($8.90) and gotta say it tastes absolutely the same as savouring it right there. Give it a pass if you hate the taste of carcinogenic charred meat with a passion - coz they consistently get it right!

There are hits and miss on my visit to this restaurant. Firstly i made a reservation at 3pm on the same day dinner but was given a seat near the entrance away from the pond which i prefer. No Queue when i reached at 7pm as this venue can hold quite a number of patrons. Order was taken fast and served promptly. London duck was served tender with sweet mango sauce. But the pieces was cut rather huge with bones therefore tougher to eat with utensils. As for the spinach with eggs and clams, taste just so-so like any other zhi char. As for the triple mushroom with asparagus, it has a unique truffle flavour gravy which rarely found in other zhi char stores. The pomelo mango dessert was poor standard with dried pomelo and no mango cubes to bring out the sweetness of this dessert. If have the chance, should give a try to the other famous dishes from this past Google reviews.
Quality of food was pretty good for ala carte buffet dinner. Good customer service.

The salted egg Prata is something you seldom find else where

Prata is crispy
Do sai is good too

The butter chicken is my favourite

Drinks are ok ok de
Value for money.  Skillful chinese cooking.  Good selection of authentic china chinese dishes to choose from.  Food portion is good.
Moved to new location. Best Mee Rebus I have. Lots of chicken. Satay sauce
The Claypot Chicken rice is as good as per expected. Mee Hoon is the best amongst. However, the KL black noodles is too salty.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Decent Hunan style dishes. The eggplant is excellent!

Cheap and value for money! It can be hard to find something different to eat that is halal in Toa Payoh and this was not bad! A bit far to walk from MRT though and service was a bit slow though there was no crowd. But food was good for the price!

Enjoyed the mala frog legs and sweet & sour pork very much!! Sweet and sour pork is crispy, the mala sauce is very good with rice. Service is good too. Probably next time I will tell them not to deep fry the frog legs ((: (personal preference)

A small eatery serving Putien, Nanyang, and some local specialties such as hainanese chicken rice. Service was good and fast. Staff are friendly and patient. The place is small and a little cramp. Very open and near shoppers passing by. Ordered the Putien Lor Mee, kang kong, crispy baby squid and xiao long pau. Food was reasonably ok. The xiao long pau was good but I've had better. The squid was crispy but packed the semi sweetness it needs. Noodles and veg were good. Tasty.

As per the brand, it‚Äôs fish ball noodles are closely associated with Malaysian taste. The fish balls are slightly softer in texture. Both fish balls and fish cakes are tasty. The mee pok is very well cooked with very good texture. Worth a try if mee pok is not your regular choice of noodle.

Food is alright. However wait time for food took more than an hour. Had to check in multiple times with staff to get follow up.

Ordering and payment was done through a QR code on the table using our mobile phones. Lots of times sold out on the menu. However, we were later informed that orders sometimes get lost in the system. Felt that if this was a problem, then this should be communicated to us first thing when seating us. Frankly, would have cancelled and left if it weren‚Äôt for the fact that we have already paid and it seems like they probably will take an even longer time to process the refund.
Veg uttapam nice to taste

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content:
everything look delicious and truly do.
love the smell and taste!!
must come and try!
I cant endure too much spicy, so I ask them to adjust.
a new choice for me now in CBD
Food is nice and price is fair.

Great vibes for great value meals.
Grab the promotion items!
usually less crowded than other places nearby. if dont want to waste time queue, can come here.

First time trying out douraku sushi by Tung lok, their Donburi was awesome! The quality of the food way surpass the price of it. Look at my photo below and you will understand why.

<bora chirashi don> we are usually quite selective when comes to sashimi as we are concerned about the freshness. To our surprise not only the look is appealing, the cut was pretty fresh too! Yumz

<Unagi don> pleasant to find that it comes with an onsen egg and jelly fish salad too. Love the egg as it add on to the moisture of the rice. The only thing that, the unagi is on the slightly saltier side, it would have been perfect if it‚Äôs lighter in the marination.

Both dons come with a seaweed soup too! Can you believe it that above order only cost $16? Yes.. it‚Äôs super worth it!!!

"An ode to Bond girl turned interior designer Anouska Hempel", and therefore quite the spot to find our chimps on ladies night. We swung over to this utopia of sophistication for our fix of pre-dinner cocktails and experienced modern Chinese creations with an emphasis on sustainability.

We loved their signature roast duck as a bar snack on a previous visit, and had returned for a full portion this time. It was therefore disappointing that the duck had sold out even before dinner time. We feel that any self-respecting restaurant should never run out of their signature dish. That is, after all, what many of the customers come for.

Here's our very own "monkey head" rating (out of 5):

One of the first (I think) kind in Singapore with individual hot pot.

No need to share if you are particular about sharing.

Service is good. Food is fresh.
The product is misleading. Not the usual size compared to the standard pau size. Attached photo for you guys to verified yourself. Photo 1 - them, photo 2 others. Same price

Very bad attitude from the CHINA lady. The plastic bag was so undersized. The tray can‚Äôt even seat in properly. End up the sauce had flow out to the plastic bag. So stingy to give customers such a small bag.

Always hearty meals here at the good ol' Jack's Place! Even kid's meals are pretty full sized! The familiar western selections, and that potato with skin topped with a heapful of sour cream, bacon bits and spring onions! We were there to celebrate the boys birthday and service was impeccable, constantly checking if everything was fine! :)
Tasty food and great service by the staff here, which are both attentive and polite. Food is a little pricey, but the dining atmosphere is comfortable.

Excellent food and service, ambience was eclectic and nice. Servers were prompt and friendly, we had the beef bowl and iberico pork bowl, both were wonderful. Come at lunch for their sets, value for money, and the food is outstanding! We will be back :)
Really bad customer service taking more than an hour to serve. The NTU branch is the worst, I would suggest you to go somewhere!

Check out ig: @oyinshii

Authentic thai restaurant with extremely great flavors! Staff were friendly and we strongly recommend the steamed fish, pad thai and yom yum gong.
Food is tasty but the side dish for dosa idly pongal not enough.they are giving very less.eventhough they will provide again.but we need to see the server face to ask our needs.cofee was not tasty.

Had the jumbo cockles from Ang Mo Kio branch block 107 coffeeshop. Fresh stock and the chilli sauce came in 4 types. The boss is super nice and friendly, go all the way to accommodate my cravings. Even offer to reserve the table for me. Will definitely go back again.

one of the to go mala when in toa payoh
price is quite ok and service is fast
The only halal food stall in this hawker center. Serving nice Indonesia and local delights such as lontong, tempeh, nasi lemak, and rendang.

Love the Ultimate series of dishes! I tried the Das Pratwurst which had yummy sausages inside, paired with curry and sauerkraut. The maggi goreng is excellent as usual too. Quick service and no-fuss meal. Thumbs up!
Sathi sorru and Fish head curry simply to die for. Simply excellent

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: The service is good, the waitress are friendly eventhough they're extremely busy. Price is affordable and the venue is fully air conditioned. The food however is a little bit of a let down, but don't let my review stop you from going there, as they say different people different preference.

My favourite hidden gem at Tai Seng! It really is quite hidden at the 2nd floor of an office building. Obviously you can tell I love this place because I have 5 photos of the pok√© bowl from different occasions (and many more I ate but didn‚Äôt take photos of). It‚Äôs operated by a group of Thai women and so they offer this sauce called spicy yum, which is the green stuff you see in the photos. I believe it‚Äôs the Thai seafood sauce made of basil, mint, chilli and other good stuff. Love!!!

Salad bowls start at $7.90, pok√© bowls are $11.90 and $15.90 for one and two salmon/tuna topping respectively. Usually ‚Äúpremium‚Äù toppings like tobiko, jellyfish or onsen egg are NOT charged extra.

Also great service and very receptive to BYO, although the salad dressing always comes prepackaged in a small plastic container so I ask them to pour it in directly sometimes.

Nice decor and service staff earned the 2 stars. Nothing much to comment about the food, we don't feel it is worth to pay for the price. Even takeaway sushi from competitive outlets are better tasting and presented. The rice grain used is not authentic for their Don bowl. Do look into the presentation and ingredients' freshness.

content:
The portion is super generous

The jampong soup is so delicious
The sweet sour chicken is on point

Waiters are very attentive to your needs

Will come back again to try the other dishes

For those who didn‚Äôt know. You be surprising that this well-liked seafood restaurant hide inside an Industrial Estate at Ang Mo Kio.

Kian Seng Seafood Restaurant @ 4013 Ang Mo Kio Industrial Park 1 #01-450 (Food Centre) S(569629)

Nice Chinese Cuisine ‚Ä¢ Live Seafood ‚Ä¢ Signature Nonya Curry Fish Head ‚Ä¢

Also provide catering and delivery services for event.

Try it next time you came to Ang Mo Kio.
Nice tender pork chops..

My go to place for a bowl of tasty Penang Hae Mee soup.

I liked its authentic, robust and strong flavours.

Only thing missing? Hard boiled egg.
Service good and food is also good.

Di San Xian (Fried Potato, Eggplant and Pepper in Garlic Sauce Âú∞‰∏âÈ≤ú)
This dish is delicious, no doubt!

Finally found a jjajangmyeon in sg that I really like. Not too sweet.
Sweet and sour pork was nice too.
The only disappointment was the jjamppong.. I really liked the soup but..there were only noodles, tonnes of onions, some bits of cucumber and 1 tiny piece of squid in it.. For the price we are paying..($40 for the set as shown in the photos) just feel that there should be more seafood in the ‚Äúseafood‚Äù noodles.. not just 1 tiny piece of squid.

Knowing how much calories is in a bowl of ramen.. this is not quite worth my calories in my opinion. To be fair.. it's not bad.. but I won't say I like it. Soup base was average, noodles was average, everything was a tad average. Pricing wise it doesn't match ramen shops in the malls (which is the right thing to do).
Pricey but delicious. Inexperienced staff but still gd service.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content:
Came here for a late lunch.

Ordered Basil Pork Rice, Clear Tom Yum Soup and their Omelette.

Basil Pork Rice was not bad. Flavour is more towards Thai taste buds.
Tom yum soup was good. Spicy and flavourful  with fish, prawn, tomatoes, onion, shimeji mushroom.
The omelette was not bad. Oily but could be crispier.

Overall a decent meal at a good price
I like the taste of the Thai food here. However, I won't recommend takeaways as I find that the taste of the food changes when I got the food home.

The food is generally decent but the staff attitude is hopeless.

I ordered a takeaway and was given a number buzzer. A staff came by and left my takeaway next to all the food orders on the table next to me. Not a single word that it was mine. The buzzer did not go off.

It was only 5 min later when I realised it was my order and asked the staff why noone told me it is mine.

This is the second time I have to deal with poor attitude from this branch.

Dined there at a quarter past 9 on a week day. Managed to find parking after circling the neighborhood twice.

Restaurant was quiet; only four tables occupied. Was told that our claypot rice would take around 25 minutes to prepare. Lucky for us, it arrived earlier.

Ordered medium size claypot rice. To be honest, at $13.80, it does feel a bit pricey. Fortunately, it tastes okay.

Ordered a small plate of their San Lou Bee Hoon. It was a first for me and my father liked it. Yes. It's dry. But that's how it should be.

Customer service is what you'd normally get from a well-mannered Foreign talent from the middle Kingdom.

In conclusion, tastes okay. But if you factor in the price, I reckon it's a wee bit pricey. Parking and seating will most definitely be an issue during peak periods. Will come back again just to let my mother try the food here.

Tried the Mushroom sauce chicken chop.
The sauce is actually pretty rich in flavor.
Chicken is tender, portions of main and sides are good.
Disappointed in the mac and cheese however.
Was expecting cold dish but somehow it‚Äôs warm and can‚Äôt taste the cheese.
Overall satisfied anyway. $7.90
Love it for the really authentic Thai food served at a very affordable neighborhood hawker price . The staffs are very friendly.

Great when you need to catch a Chinese meal at Velocity, in Novena area. The beef noodle soup with tendon and brisket was flavorful. Brisket was tender (think it's slow-cooked?) and I usually don't like brisket but finished all of it. The noodle would be even better if the soup came steaming hot, an essential trait for Chinese style noodles.
Premium taste at cheap cost ! :)

Never thought that we could find such a gem at international plaza. Kia hiang serves really good traditional chinese food, even my korean colleagues love this place. Must try their claypot chicken, its superb!

content:
taste good but service super lowsy. At first the lady who took my order was very blur. Confirmed with me twice but still placed the wrong order. 3 people work as waiter keep walking in the restaurant and checking my order slip every time when they pass by my table. but they dont even know what is my order. After main dish and rice served they took another 20mins to serve me side dish and soup of the day.

dont come during peak hour.
Good quality food and presentation at an affordable price

Bot some pau and har gao...fresh and delicious. However disappointed with the fun choy...seem to have kept for some time...apparently staff did not observed slow moving food...Price is a bit stiff in this neighborhood area...though the packing is reasonable good.

Had breakfast here on 7th March. Service was really tardy. Wanted to order a Tandoori and maggi goreng special and was told that Tandoori chicken is not available till 11am. Looked at the watch and told him it's 3 mins to 11am and then was told the chef is not here yet. Changed the order to just maggi goreng and Uttapam.

Uttapam came first followed by maggi goreng. Food was served without utensils. Uttapam was not too bad and it was my first time having them. As for Maggi goreng, it was very salty. Honestly felt that the price paid for the food and quantity as well as nonexistent service is way too much. I'm sure there are better options around.
Great satay and a very unique mashed sweet potato gravy mee rebus that is a little heavy for one person, so maybe share it.

Food: 4/10
Cost: $
Recommended food: Ribeye Beef Steak

Drove all the way to Toa Payoh to check out what's the hype with this neighbourhood western food that was featured in quite a few news articles and food reviews. Sad to say it is not really worth the hype. The ribeye cost 15 dollars which is quite reasonablely price, however in terms of taste it just tasted like most neighbourhood western food, of course those good ones. The pork chop is medicore, nothing special. In conclusion, the western food here is very average in terms of taste, and it serve well as a neighbourhood western food, but definitely not worth to specially travel down for food tasting.

Recommend by friend. 1st tried. As Malaysian I think these was far from Authentic. But if crave it, don‚Äôt aspect too high. I think ‚ÄúMalaysia Boleh‚Äù laksa better then this and Ipoh curry mee yishun Industrial Street was nice than here. But the environment here was pretty good and the Ipoh white coffee is nice.

The Lobster Thermidor was very well cooked: The salad was fresh and the butter rice was flavorful. The amount of cheese and cream on the lobster was generous and was delicious with the lobster meat.

Jack's Special steak was also great except it was slightly overcooked from what we wanted.

Atmosphere-wise the place was quite loud so don't expect a cosy quiet experience.
Go for the claypot rice and seafood bee hoon as they are the signature dishes. You will have to roll the dice if you wanna try other dishes.

(Translated by Google) Nice rice cake

(Original)
Nice lontong

Delicious, affordable.

Had the basic buta don (set thanks to the lunch promo), base price was $11 before tax.

Verdict? Really good. The pork was nice and tender and the seasoning makes you hungrier. Rice was packed nicely and fills you up well.

Eating companion took chicken nanban ($11) and it was good as well. The tartar sauce and karrage seasoning went well together.

Will be back to try the other stuff.

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Worst experience in pickup. Waited more than 30 mins and they keep on ask us to wait. Finally collected order after 1 hour.

Cafe located in toa Payoh central. Decent selection of food, taste is not bad but a little pricey. Food takes quite long to be served. Interesting ice cream flavours available here. Cash, nets or grab pay payment only. Unique decorations.
Good Quality Japanese food. Service is very fast even when the restaurant is packed. Staff here are also friendly.

Quality of food and service can be improved. Needs more manpower.

Edit: Management should improve on customer service (polite to customers and not ignoring them) and the food served instead of engaging fake accounts to boost the score. This will increase the value of the experience and attract more customers to come back again.
Not bad..
Cashier lady was rude. Food was mediocre

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content:
Didn‚Äôt took photo as waited too long And very hungry...
Maybe because I have tried other stall that suit my taste more.. a bit disappointed.
Soup is ok. The pan doesn‚Äôt stick at all, price very cheap compare to other place.
So that all for the 2 star.
Marinated meat don‚Äôt suit my taste.

I'm... so... shockingly sad. :( Ordered a Medium Rare Fillet Mignon, it came presentable but when I tried to cut it, the meat was so tough. Took forever to chew as well. The picture below speaks for itself. I forced myself to finish it as it cost $30+. Really felt like crying as it was the worst beef I've eaten and I'm not even a "steak expert". Just want to warn future diners what they're in for - Very tough meat and microwaved vegetables.
(also, iced water is served with one ice cube lol)
This review is made on September 2021.

Visited at off peak hours to enjoy their 40% off food ingredients deal. Definetly worth it and their tomato soup base was definitely one of the best out there, and the food ingredients we ordered was good too as well.
Good and delicious food at very affordable price....
One of the best outlets. A bit warm as usual. Good is fantastic üëåüòä

The food is good.. i enjoyed my sirloin steak and my folks enjoy the food they ordered.. but the order taking got messed up. We ordered a seafood mixed combo but was served a beef mixed combo.. maybe the naming should differ so as to prevent mixed up.. overall its ok, we came for the food afterall

Get the Blanched Red Grouper w Seafood Pepper Stock (Infused with Lobster, Prawns & Crabs). Topped with crackling crispy rice when it hits the soup. Skip the truffles and stick to the traditional Chinese dishes imo. A little on the pricier end for Chinese food but well worth the money.

Ala carte buffet dinner at reasonable prices. Staff service was good. Dishes delivered via conveyor belt system. Reducing much wait time. Ordering via online menu after scanning a QR code givevn by staff was also quick and simple.

Service was attentive and thoughtful. Staff were very accommodating and fulfilled our request to change to another table (although only after a second request) even though they were very busy. Drinks were topped up promptly. But do take note that there is an interesting charge of $2.50 per head even if you do not drink tea, eat the peanuts or use the wet towels. Food was good but not spectacular.

Have Been Wanting To Visit For Times... So It's Like Finally~
Is Definitely Worth To Visit Cafe...
Nice Ambience, Nice Food!!
Baked Escargots 4/5 üëç (It'll Be Perfect If More Garlic Are Added)
Mushroom Truffle Melts 3/5 (Was A Little Disappointed w Their Crust Though)
Pork Ribeye Steak 4/5 üëç
Grilled Salmon 4/5 üëç
*WAFFLES* 4/5 üëç

Loved the interior design and spacious. Also has an outdoor sheltered seating area. Our group of 3 had the croffles with fried chicken, the crispy chicken burger, the rosti with mushrooms & pork sausages, chicken tenders with korean spicy sauce - all of them were decently good. The letdown came in the form of their tarts where the crust was soft, and it just felt liked it was kept for too many days.
The combo set was a disappointment. There was any chicken meat at all for the chicken. Lots of skin and fats.
Tried the Ireland Peking Duck. Very good. Promotion $58. Usually price $88. Worth it. Ireland duck bigger and more juicy than the normal duck.
Great food at very reasonable prices. Just happened to stop by and try. Recommended ! Friendly service too~
If can more vegetarian food is better
Is this Bestari? The drink stall lady was very rude when she served me. When I complained of the coconut in the super cooler drink has already turned bad, she refused to replace it.

Our usual Sat dinner at Jurong point, decide to try the new ramen restaurant since there is no queue. I know that I should order the ramen but was craving for rice so end up ordering a unagi toji don and it did not disappoint. Rice was soft and savoury, together with the well cooked unagi, it was pretty delicious. She got the limited lobster ramen and it came with a plastic glove, napkin, crab scissor and a wet wipe! Attention to details is amazing and the broth did not disappoint. Initially think that it could too thick but it wasn't, it was easy to drink and has a good punch of seafood taste. Noodle was good and lobster was not overcooked.

Rating: 8/10
I am coming back to try the remaining ramen!
Do come and try!
