Great tasting food at affordable prices.
Great food at affordable prices. If you're looking for cheap western food, this is it!

Is been a year didn‚Äôt came back here breakfast.
I rmr my previous experience was the place are super crowded, waiting time too long.

Today went for early breakfast.
Surprisingly the the food taste better then last time ü§£ good !

Overall their foods is good, price wise slightly higher (if compare normal hawker), but they are aircon & nice deco environment so consider reasonable.

Recommend the Ipoh kopi , not so sweet n the taste jz nice.
Excellent service with amazing food. Compliment to Aunty chun Hong, my daughter made the place messy and she was very nice to offer tissue and water for her.
Enjoyed the braised lobster with bee hoon and leek ($120 for 1.2kg). The soup had a nice flavour. The spinach with three eggs was good.
That's only word can say "yummy" and reasonable price.

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: Very bad service. Not heeding to customers‚Äô needs
very nice fish ball ! fish cake is awesome too ! noodles are nice , tried both mee kia dry and kway teow soup . long queue though but worth the wait . highly recommended!
The tomyam noodle soup is the best.

Came here since last visited Jack‚Äôs Place a few years ago. It is one of the old branch where it had its standalone restaurant. Order the chicken chop in hotplate and served with their signature potato with servings.  Below are the pictures of other dish such as salmon and curly onion fries

Quite a gem to be located far from town. Served warmly local cuisine that we all familiar with in Zhi Char. The price commanded quite high compare to the standard of the food. Came here multiple times and probably I have tried the Irish such and field KL Hokkien noodle the best! Don‚Äôt miss these 2 dishes. The fry chives with prawn was disappointing. Prawn is way over cooked and taste hard. The fry fermented tofu pork is too dry.. over frying ! The chili cockles was so so as it is too small for you to feel shiok especially the sauce used wasn‚Äôt prepared well. The fry salted egg fish skin can be improved as the skin not as crispy. The pork collar is rather so so and bland. The ouster way too big to enjoy and not briny! Disappointing wither the soon hock fish, overcooked and the meat kind too tough and dry. The other plus point was the corkage is free and friendly restaurant owner to cheer with you from time to time.
Ok place

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content: Had the prata kosong and as others have reported, it was good! Teh tarik was quite sweet and wife's Maggi goreng was decent but took some time to come. Service was functional and efficient as with your usual mamak shop. Overall, not a bad place to satisfy your prata cravings.

I have ordered from this McDonald's twice, and both times I was given the wrong food. First, I got a burger instead of McNuggets, and the the second time I was given chicken wings instead of a McChicken. Dissappointed. Just wanted some nugs...

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Service staff was great on 25may's dinnertime, everyone was very friendly and efficient as well. Food not amazing, couple of items not replenished since we stepped in and taste wise also just mediocre, but soup base actually quite authentic....
Horrible portion.  Threw away the food after seeing the pathetic portion and no more appetite.
Air conditioned food court with mookata and beer options. Beer is cash only, so bring some along. Social distancing is minimal, plus some people working there don't really put on their masks.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: This stall sells on hybrid between Nasi Lemak with Taliwang grilled chicken (one of Indonesian speciality dish).. the coconut infused rice is very tasty and the grilled chicken is tender.. the staff also very friendly..

Had a highly enjoyable dinner here. Fantastic value and freshness for an ala carte buffet. Dishes are all cooked upon order and are zichar classics.Dishes all come in tasting portions so you have a chance to order from the wide range of dishes. Highly recommended. No photos this time as was too busy eating. üòÑ
Definitely get the fish for your choice of meat because they'll fry it really nicely for you! (Potato and lotus root as well) Scrambled egg is very fluffy too :)

Fantastic curry! I had the dried curry and soup, its about 80% close to what I can get in Ipoh! Had the nasi lemak and the anson special chee cheong fun, it was okay, nothing crazy good about it. The white coffee is good though, its creamy yet not too sweet. Love it! Overall, I quite like it!

Very nice Nasi Padang famous for their beef rendang. The beef Rendang is not bad but I had better elsewhere. Each individual dish was very very well made. In fact this is a stall that you can eat daily without getting bored of the dishes.Very 'home-cooked' feel. Highly recommended. Must try the beef rendang and see if it's as claimed haha.

i used to be regular few years back. But now a days tried to avoid. Few simple reasons, lunch is ridiculously priced 9.7$ and other items also price they have increased. They are using very small containers,  which is not enough for any one .. less sambar, curries, and dahi etc. Comparatively simillar resturants  give better quantity and quality food.
. but the price is high. Also most of the time i buy i find something is missing they forgot to keep. simply they say sorry if you call up. and ridiculously  late no proper order have noticed  many times ppl order same food ex. lunch after me have got it and took .. and yet  we need to wait...it is poor service.. i dun recommend this place. Sorry guys i was a fan b4 and now it is pain and frustrated....
Almost always crowded but service and food is always good!

Amazing stuff. The curry had such aromatic and deep flavours to it I can't say I've had anything like it before; and the lady's fingers were some of the tastiest I've ever had - very tender and flavorful. Of the bunch I'd say the otah is the least impressionable - quite flat and bland. My wife had the lotong and she's full of priase for it as well. The food is a little more pricey than average but I think it's certainly worth it. Highly recommended! üòãüëçüèª

Cosy zi char place! Food is fragrant and tasty. The ubin lala beehoon has good wok hei and the lala is very fresh. They are generous with the egg too. The marmite pork ribs were a little hard but was ok overall. The belacan Kang Kong was delicious, though a little bit on the salty side! Staff were courteous and friendly. Highly recommended place for dinners w bigger groups. You can make reservation here via Chope.
Japanese oysters not on the menu, quite fresh and tasty! Fried rice portion a bit small but taste wise is good üëç

Quality of food is always there üòã for the past 2 yrs. For 3/4 of us, we  ordered small size dishes and medium for noodles;  pretty good value for money.

Need to queue a while during Friday night dinner hours.

I‚Äôve never had such a bad sashimi in my life. Not well chilled, not fresh (tuna sashimi is almost black color) and awfully presented at a high price. You‚Äôd better throw your money into the wishing pond than wasting money on these sashimi that can get you poisoned. Living in this area for 3 years without trying this shop and this will be my last time. Crazy that this restaurant is still open, probably because of the 10++ Ashahi beer which is good. Should avoid at all cost if you‚Äôre craving for raw fish.

The food was so disappointing. As a start, why is there corn in the ramen soup‚Ä¶

Service was extremely slow.

A5 wagyu was good tho‚Ä¶. Cuz it wasn‚Äôt cooked by them‚Ä¶ beer also‚Ä¶..

Summary : come here if you want Japanese music, anime pictures around and some beer from the tap.
Service was good. Foods are delicious. Always kept their standard. Sashimi is fresh.

First time trying with the wife as the reviews sounded promising. Ordered a spicy beef burrito set and a spicy pulled pork bowl set. Both were very disappointing... Very little meat in both, just lots of tasteless rice and beans... Miserable amount of salsa given. Food was barely even warm considering we were dining in... Chips were obviously stale. Not sure if they forgot to put the spice but both the orders were not spicy at all... "Chipotle" Fries, while cooked well, crunchy outside soft inside, tasted completely plain and devoid of any seasoning... Not sure if the outlet ran out of salt or what... The only thing that we both managed to finish was the lemon tea... Have tasted real Mexican food and this is not even close sorry. Went to McDonald's after...
Really delicious and too many great choices. Queue was long but we were lucky to get our seats. Would eat here again when Im around next time!
Nice and affordable. Good for a weekend meal.

Simply best.
Must try the channa bhaturaüòã
Good choice for Vegetarians
Batang fish soup is great! Fresh fish and flavourful soup. Small serving serves at most 2 pax imo.

Awful experience.

1) standing at the entrance, waiting to be seated. This lady looked at us but ignored us.

2) the other staff (uncle) escorted us in after waiting for 3mins. While seated, I raised my hand for a good 5minutes but nobody came to us. One of us shouted excuse me, order! This staff lady in photo saw and heard us but she just did not care. Most probably she thinks she is only in charge of serving drinks and not taking orders. However, she also does not inform her colleagues to take our order.

I understand that you are understaffed during the peak hour on a Friday dinner. But your service could have been a lot better. This lady really just looked at us and ignored us.

We are big fans of Sushi Tei but the last time we dine here we made a mistake of ordering a supposedly ramen noodles that came as reinvented Instant Noodles with saut√©ed onion, chives, meat and egg. That was the biggest disappointment, we were looking forward for a decent ramen. We ordered a plate of Sushi with supposedly crispy salmon skin at the centre but that too failed us, it was gummy and chewing was a struggle.

We still love Sushi Tei but next time probably stick to the safer and premium choices we've always loved.

Very good food, not too crowded for a weekend lunch. Food is not cheap but very tasty and service is good. My favourites were the stir fried  asparagus with black fungus and pine nuts,  sweet and sour pork and various dimsum dishes
Super shiok supper food. Bee Hoon Goreng, not dry and not too wet, justtttt right. Huge portion too, can share for 2 pax.

Didn't know this place existed so I decided to have a try with my friends on a Monday afternoon. Big portions and value for money üëçüèΩ Will come back again to try out the other stuff from the menu.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Ordered Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang for lunch. Also added a fish fillet because I am greedy! Haha! üòÇ The chicken meat was so tender and it fall off the bone easily! But for someone like me with low tolerance to spice, the chilli was very spicy and I broke out in sweat after a few spoonfuls of it! üî•ü•µ Overall it‚Äôs really a good and tasty Nasi Lemak in Yishun so please consider to give it a try if you are here! üòã
poor service , auntie seemed reluctant to serve and showed black face
So good, excellent ,  the soup, noodle, meat... Fantastic..
Wok hei food here

Been coming here for 3 years, and it is consistently very good. Love the shenyan dumplings, Mapo tofu, and Dan Dan noodles. Probably the best Chinese restaurant in Singapore. Lovely food and great service!
I enjoy my black bean sauce hor fun and prawn sauce chicken alot. The coffee pork ribs was not to my liking as it was too bitter. The price was reasonable and definately will return
Friendly staff! Amazing food! They sell the best Indian rojak in Singapore!

Highly recommend this humble restaurant. Food was great, portion is good and value for money! I highly recommend the rib eye, the otoro wrap, egg plant as side dish and also the cold udon!!! Thank you Nareenth and Zamzi for your great service too!

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: I gave it my first try recently and it was amazing! The beef rendang was cooked to perfection; each bite more tender than the previous. The chicken wings had a really strong flavour to it too which I personally love. The sayur lodeh was good, but I only had 3 pieces of sayur... Was a little taken aback by that. Nonetheless, parking can be a pain in the area so do avoid peak hours. The queue was fast. In and out in less than 5 during peak hour on a weekday, Post-Cb.

Fast, clean. Slightly advantage in the varieties,  so can order what your personal  that you like. Quality is  higher and among the best

Fast sushi but good place to have decent peaceful catch-up meals without rushing in a busy shopping centre environment.  This one sitted side by side (abit more diff but will do)

Discovered it after my haircut nearby. Quality was good but a tad pricey for coffee shop location. Compared to nearby stalls with average prices of $3 and up, the ramen special bowl is $10.90. But it was tasty and looked and tasted authentic. Onsen egg was good, a whole large piece of nori seaweed and generous 4 thick slices of chashu. I recommend. Worth a visit.
Taste like regular mcdonald's, price is the same as non institutional outlets

If you want black bean noodles (jjajangmyeon) this is the place to go to! The noodles were springy and chewy and the sauce was smoky and complex.

But take note of the long queue. I had to wait 45 minutes for a table on a Friday evening. The queue only got longer later into the evening

Very good Chinese food but comes at a hefty price! Portions are small, like tapas servings. Service is good and server was able to recommend/advice dishes and it‚Äôs portions to ensure sufficient for our dinner party.

Crispy roast pork belly super yums! Szechuan spicy fried chicken and mee sua highly recommended! Egg plant dish too! Couldn‚Äôt think of an average dish as all of awesome!

Perfect for special occasions and suitable for business entertainment as the ambience is very stylish and luxurious.

IG @iambruisedlee

I ordered 5 food via grab food. They delivered only 4 and the items also different. When I make a call to the manager, she said to collect from their restaurant. She refused to arrange the delivery. So rude
Food was great. Recommended to book in advance. Really enjoyed their signature prawns.

There was a queue in front of my favorite mee rebus and Nasi lemak stall.   The owner spotted me and remarked 'your leg hurts right.   Go sit down, I will bring your Bkfast to you...'.  This is my heartland, my Singapore.. my Xmas.
Not bad can give it a shot, garlic sauce not too strong and portion reasonable
China woman was very rude. I'll never dine here again

restaurant name: Anjana Kitchen - Best Indian Restaurant Singapore
content: Very good indian food. Not too salty n reasonable price. My fav masala dosa, naan n briyani

This is the 2nd vegetarian restaurant I would recommend. The food are really very nice and tasty. As it is pretty popular, make sure you make reservation ahead. And do note that they only allow you to stay for 1.5 hrs which is actually more than sufficient to allow others to have a chance to taste the food as well.
Enjoyed the tasty soto babat and chicken, mee rebus babat and chicken  as well as the babat and mutton satay. Service was good.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Hot, delicious and the right amount of flavor. Their business is buzzing even with restrictions. Always order hor fun or fish head bee hoon, and many others and every one of them taste good!

So bad order received.  Pay money but give like water as curry????
Vegetarian food 2 meals nothing vegetables. Given fish curry???
Tasteless food like this i payed $27.50
Money not eassy to get please understand.
U can review my order and what u given to us.
Delivery fee $4.89 for deliver this kind of food.
If u all cannot deliver as we order pls cancel our order instead giving ths kind of food.

Closed on Monday. Usually sold out by 11am(before the 2pm closing time). Mainly for breakfast since the fishballs are not enough to last beyond lunch. Fishball are very nice. Real fish meat without added starch. Silky smooth and bouncy chew.. My favourite. Noodles are Malaysia style (black sauce) so if u like the tomatoe ketchup type... This is not for you. The chilli dry noodle taste better than the non chilli. U can request the soup for all fishball if you are not a fan of fishcake and taohu. $4small $5big noodle. $4.50 fishball soup standard size. Overall is good.
Good food

Wow.. I'm surprised by the Naan!
And Masala Tea is sold here!
Been here a few times but always feel nothing special. Until I realized they sell masala tea here. I loved masala tea and they did it well.

Have tried their fried rice and noodles but ok only la. Then today finally tried their naan and wow.

I ordered the Garlic Naan with butter chicken. Butter chicken is okay nice,
But It's the Naan that's special. Never see before naan is like that. Soft, Puffy yet chewy like as though got mozzarella but I didn't order cheese naan so it's not. It's just the texture of the naan that's somewhat stretchy like mozzarella , puffy airy soft like bread yet you eat and know it's still a naan.

Highly recommended to eat naan and masala tea here.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Fried chicken is good but a bit stingy on the portion of army stew...

Finished all our food, totally wiped clean. Great quality food, pleasant and warm service staff, consistently good, family friendly, a bit pricey to the wallet, but it‚Äôs really decent quality Cantonese dim-sum. Generous Portion and nice for a family dinner together.

Ordered their Yang-Zhou fried rice - 5/5, can be shared with 3 person,
we had steamed rice roll with fried bean curd - 4/5, extremely tasty and need to be shared or it becomes ‚Äòjelat‚Äô.
Steamed pork-bun, nice char siew filling....
Prawn steamed dumpling aka Xiao long bao - decent, but can make their skin thinner...
Steamed pork meat dumpling in chili oil... nice! It‚Äôs not too spicy and ‚Äònumb-ing‚Äô!

All in all, I love the experience and I will certainly come back for more!

restaurant name: Rathana Bhavan Indian Vegetarian Restaurant (B2 Kopitiam) - Yishun North Point
content: Waited 20minutes for a plate of fried rice. Very bad service.

Initially when I saw all the bad reviews about this place in Google and all the good reviews in Xiao Hong Shu, I thought this must be a case of non Chinese nationals disliking authentic Shanghainese flavours. So I decided to give it a try. I was wrong.

First there was the long wait, which is expected for a new restaurant offering Shanghainese food. We were a group of 3 and when it was our turn, we were seated at a table meant for two only. Just make do, we were told. If and when a table frees up, the waiter promised to shift us. Never did, even after more than one table frees up.

Food wise, we ordered the Sheng Jian Bao, Beef Guo Tie, Scallion oil Noodles, Chilli Oil Dumplings, Crab meat dumpling soup and Drunken Chicken. The dumplings, Sheng Jian Bao all tasted sweet without the umami of meat juice coming from steamed fresh meat. Someone in the kitchen took the idea of adding a little sugar, to elevate the taste of the dumpling filling, too far. The scallion oil noodles had too little scallion taste as the noodles was a disproportionately large serving. Only the beef potstickers and drunken chicken impressed, the former because it is a rarity and the latter because it tasted genuinely good. And I should know because I lived in Shanghai for almost 20 years.

Service was polite but inadequate. We were left sitting there to twiddle our thumbs for 10 mins without menu nor means to order using their QR code.

Not coming back anytime soon.
The pork ribs were tender and the portion was quite big. Value for money at $16.

Bad attitude from staff, was waiting for takeaway orders. Kept having to ask if our order is ready, staffs said no but later on we found out it was ready long ago.

When took back home, found out that one of the rice packet was not air tight secured. Circuit breaker is a dangerous time, would you dare to eat dishes which are not well contained and exposed to the air surroundings of a covid infested mall?

It's closest to home cooked food that you can find. There is no msg in the food and the taste is genuine. Had their signature lobster porridge. The lobsters are very fresh and the size is around 300gm each so the piece of meat is quite decent. The 3 eggs vege dish is very good and so is stir fried red garouper filler meat. The tofu is really smooth and you can actually taste the bean. Price is very reasonable.

Nice place to have some hawker fares. The wanton Mee is pretty average, the current chicken noodles is good0,, chicken rice is good. Chendol is great too. Good clean tables and the cleaner is quite efficient too

(Translated by Google) I ordered sweet and sour pork loin, and I was charged at the original price. I only saw the discount information when I went out, and I said that the order cannot be changed. Tired, will not go again.

lamb chop was delicious and staff are friendly. only nit is the hot grill plate has ridges which makes cutting the lamb chop difficult. also the lamb chop gets overcooked on the grill plate. plus side of it is your food stays hot longer. perhaps have a tiny discount (something like 20-50cents discount) for customers who opt for a less premium normal plate. that may entice customers who want a no frills chop/steak for good price to order the chops/steaks.

Average menus at average pricing... Quality of prepping not as expected.. but then it was advertised as affordable Japanese cuisine nonetheless. 3 stars because of courteous and kind staffs. May not return though.

The appetiser is a bit too much for 1 person, maybe they try to match the amount food to the price.. but I rather they reduce the price instead. The main course is alright but the rareness scale is a bit off to the rare side.

My wife and I ate several times there, the food was good (don't expect a candle-light dinner hey üòâ ), the staff very friendly, and the price hard to beat in Singapore (with rice/naan and curry combos at 6 SGD). I recommend!
Very local,deep in the corner.

Food portion is big and generous but doesn't taste very good. Dishes are sub par or salty. Briyani no standard. Nasi goreng is bland and soggy although generous ingredients. Basically their cooks are not skilled.

restaurant name: Nasi Lemak Ayam Taliwang - Yishun Park Hawker Centre
content: Well i saw quite a number of people Q'ing up ...And i decided to try it. I order their Nasi Lemak Set. Their Rice was fragrant. Sambal Chili is tasty and NOT too spicy. The chicken wing however the taste was so so...Average. Their Deep Fried Potato was good though. Overall i gave 4 stars ...Very good....
peking duck is nice & delicious üëçüëçüëç

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Had chargrilled chicken and 2 sides for lunch and it was an enjoyable meal. Chicken was tender and juicy while the baked potato was done right. Quiet place during weekdays for some me-time. No service charge and SAFRA members get 10% off.
Good food at reasonable price!
Cheap and good food
Over the bridge noodles are served here. Drinks include Roselle tea. And dessert is a chilled fruit jelly.

Quite a nice spot nestled deep inside AMK Ave 10 blocks. Took us a while to find the place. Food is decently priced and lunch comes with free flow of iced lemon tea.

We tried a range of items and in general the burgers was good but the Cajun grilled chicken was a bit undercooked (pinkish).

Friendly wait staff‚Ä¶.

A quiet cosy place for authentic Chinese food. Personally, I find their mapo toufu is one of the best with good silky toufu and really good spicy sauce. As I asked for original flavor  and spicineess, I really experienced that spicky kick that made my forehead break into sweat on a cold rainy evening. A bit pricey but with the good quality food, I will definitely be back to try other dishes.

Small stall in the coffee shop. Tasty Nasi Lemak
Rice texture real good with the generous chilli sauce. Chilli sauce not too spicy can taste the Bawang Yums
Crispy chicken wing n Ikan Bilis. Must add Begedil delicious tasty soft potato with not too overwhelming celery leaf taste.
3person portion plus 3 curry puff $11

Insta: ju.rine
Very average food, it's slightly pricey. The burrito was very bland, the rice in it was bland. The only thing good on the entire menu is nacho fries

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Totally worth my time and pocket . Enjoy every moment , just one thing , plan what you want to eat to avoids too much leftover . Appreciate your food . Staff are very helpful and fantastic service by the staff . Thank you so much , i would love to repeat my visit .

Although this place is convenient Indian halal food but service is slow. This restaurant look clean and no smell but too many flies.
Restaurant owner need to pay attention to address flies and organize the place.

I ordered the hotplate chicken,
End up I received the Rice without the chicken

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content:
The roasted duck,pork, char siew and soya saurce chicken plus the wan ton mee ( noodle) all taste not bad.Prices are at normal coffeeshop level.This company has quite a number of outlets around Singapore.
Dated :06/10/2017 ( Thursday ).
Update : 07/10/2019 ( Monday ).
Added 1 photo of Wanton Mee ( Yun Tun Mian ).

It's my third visit to this outlet today with my family. Food is awesome as always. On top of that, would love to specially give our compliment to staff Jun Ning on her approach to customers. It's just genuine and you can feel it from the bottom of the heart (I came from customer service line as well). Hopefully the management rewards her accordingly to her performance. I'm telling you she will be a gem to your company
nice....
We are frequent customers despite the price. Get your sauce on the side for your roti john. You'll thank me later. The murtabak is pretty good!

Wow, long queue for nasi lemak. Means must try! I realised quickly, many people were buying many packets to take aways.

Nasi lemak is ok, chicken wings seasoning was very good. I added fired fish, tasted great too.
expensive!!! expensive!!! expensive!!! It's not worth the price

Despite all the fave reviews, the place didn't quite live up to the expectations.

The food was decent and honestly nothing to shout about.

Service was less than desirable, especially when calling for a reservation. Pricing was definitely reasonable and we do really get too many hakka restaurants around, which makes this place unique.
Not really fantastic. Just a place to eat only. But popiah $$ not bad. Quite nice. Chendol also ok.
Good selection of sushi, rice sets and ramen. They also serve kids meal but the "car" tray was unstable (one wheel missing). Took quite a long time to serve the food but we enjoyed it.
Newly renovated! This is my go-to prata place in AMK. Way better than the one in Upper Thomson. Super crowded after the renovation.
Used to be good food here! Standard has dropped a lot and they skimed on the ingredients. Not worth a visit anymore.
Soup is nice and thick, sliced fish is fresh too! Went there twice in 1 week.
Good and affordable food. Although crowded but service efficiency is great. Does not take long to receive the food. Staff are well-mannered and efficient. Good things must try....ü§óü§ó

We almost ordered everything from the menu! The taste was great and the lady who served us was great. She is attentive and warm when we ordered our food.
A simple yet cosy place to visit if you just need a place to ease your Japanese food bangs. :) Keep up your great work!
We had one of the set dinners for Fathers' Day. Food was excellent, service was good.
hot and spicy mala fish

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Food here is so so good. The service has been very welcoming too! Highly recommend their eggplant dish. Out of the 6 dishes I ordered, all was amazing. Definitely coming back to try other stuff of their menu.
Always very tasty and delicious. The automated trays add a different experience from other dim sum restaurants.
Mee goreng pretty decent. Kitchen and ordering counter is on one side while seating area is across the path that pedestrians walk by, making it a little tricky.

Have tried their Lamb Briyani which was very tasty. Nice mamak place to have lunch and dinner. When I was there I could see a long queue so I assumed that this place is quite popular for this neighbourhood. My briyani was fairly portioned and I think it is fairly priced.

Nostalgic! Still as good as ever 20 years ago and  now!!! Back then my friend and I, we were really sad when we found out that the clementi stall no longer existed. Have been trying to find out if they were closed for good/relocated until in the recent years, my friend saw a fb post and found out they have relocated to AMK. Imagine how happy we were. Just last week we dropped by, had some fries while reminiscing the good old days and dabao chicken chop, fish & chips, spring chicken. Everything was delish and I already can't wait till my next visit.

108 k.m. away from Toa payoh,is a isolated kampong coffee shop,for kampong folk live near by.
When you really hungry, no choice for you, than you have to eat there!.
Visit a friends stay there, exactly like in Singapore, during 1960! More nature and kampongs, is unimproved situation , BUT,PEACEFUL, QUITE, FRESH AIR,HAPPY, SLOW MOTION, ONLY 3% stress, surrounded heavily cheap tropical fruit,and vegetable s,.  NO HOTEL!!!.
Tasty food but there was a small dead cockroach in my mocktail. Ruined an otherwise tasty lunch.

The only ramen place that you can get free Raman and additional raman for 0.50. The Raman is worth the money generous portions of the char siew. First time eat Raman and had trouble finishing the meat. They having a promotion 1 for 1 for student and the tako ball is really nice and the taro drinks with the Pearl taste great and refreshing.

Love the value the owner is giving. nowdays hawker food can cost even more than takagi.

Never had a bad dish here. Clam bee hoon has the wok taste, fluffy Oyster omlette, tasty spinach soup. Just disappointed they ran out of pork ribs and we didn't know had to order crab day in advance.

Great and attentive service too - I asked for cup of hot water to b sterilise baby's pacifier and waiter even brought tongs for it!!

I was like arriving there at 11 AM on Sunday. There were more than 15 people in the queue. So it took me about 20 minutes to take my turn. Both of noodles and the soup taste good, however a little bit salty. And I think the taste is not good enough for you to across the whole Singapore to come here. And if you are living nearby you can come here every day lol.

I love how the outdoor seating makes you feel that you are enclosed with the greenery and you do not feel like u are in a park.

food was average but we like how the staff listened to the feedback we gave to Cook the chicken liver a little less done. and they managed to perfect it !

special shout out to the staff Sam (sum) whom managed to salvage a situation we encountered while dining. he also has good knowledge in the sake there and was able to recommend to us.

would definitely visit them again.
Always love their version of the Yu Sheng.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: Those who enjoy savoury spicy authentic Indian dishes this is the right place

Nice ambience. Only managed to try the sharkfin soup, fried squid and seafood bee hoon since only 2 of us. Food was OK but the sharkfin soup was served warm instead of piping hot. The bee hoon needs improvement. Price is acceptable. Service was OK. The craft beer was nice though not cold enough.
Nice food...
Food is great but the quantity has shrunk
Great place so cozy and the food was awesome with a lot of variety dishes.
Very enjoyable fishball noodle. But portion size for the price isn't exactly good value by me.

Salty and cold. Not worth the 2 hour waiting time.
1 hr queue and 1 hr to wait for food to cook.

Once the buzzer ringed, we straight took our food. So i not sure how did that 10 second walk from their shop to our table (since it was just beside them) cooled our food immediately.
The service was impecable and the good was delicious!

This is one of those hipster coffee shops, located in the middle of nowhere, selling good food and providing good ambience. The tse char stall here Yalong Bay is pretty decent, and the coffeeshop has a very impressive collection of craft beers that are very well priced, especially in bulk. Imported San Miguel will go for 35 for 10 bottles - that's how attractive it can go.

Found this cafe through Google search and it was the 1st one that came up for "best eats near Toa Payoh mrt".. Cafe was located on the other side of Toa Payoh mall, so might need to walk abit to find it if you are not familiar with the area. Cafe was almost full on a Sunday afternoon at about 1pm and more people came after us. Indoor and outdoor seatings available. Food ordering and payment was through online, quick and efficient. Waiting time for the food was surprisingly quick, less than 10mins. Wide variety of western cuisine and desserts & beverages. Food was good and service was good too, staff were all friendly. No gst or service charge. Nice place to visit if you are in Toa Payoh area.
Good food
