The food is very delicious, and I think with no artificial flavors. The price is also not too expensive.

Worth travelling from the east to ang mo kio just to have their delicious mee soto & satay (chicken/beef). Love the mee soto gravy & the satay gravy definitely a good combination üëç Worth my money for paying these 2 delicious food that I ordered, you won't regret trying üòä

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Wee Nam Kee is a well known Hainanese Chicken Rice restaurant that also serves other Chinese dishes in its menu. However it‚Äôs really known more for its authentic and delicious Hainanese Chicken Rice. The chicken is tender, juicy, fragrant and cooked to perfection. The rice is also just right, not too oily and has enough flavor and fragrance. A Chicken drumstick set includes choice of steamed oyster vegetable (Kailan) and/or pork dumplings. I opted for both! The set also comes with either lemon tea or barley (choice of hot or cold). Superb! 4/5!

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: If you love spicy pad kaprao (thai basil pork with rice), ask for extra spicy from Hom Aroy - super yums!!

Carrot cake and stir fried oyster omelette is the worst I have ever had. The carrot cake wasn't even up to standard, the cake was NOT even CUT and was served LARGE CUBED SIZED, about the size of one's thumb or a tablespoon
Worst experience
Pretty tasty dishes..full of spices and herbs goodness..would appreciate to downsize the sugar level for healthy reasons for daily consumption otherwise is supergood for once in awhile indulgence..
for 40 years of my lifes‚Ä¶. this is one of the most worst mamak shop ever i‚Äôve encountered. There is nothing! when u order, no more everything all no more

Promotion ended but outside still put old poster. Only told us that promo ended when paying bills. Portion of one time dishes quite small for our big group of 7, not worth it when u come as a big group because the food portion same as another table of 3 or 4.
Food arrived cold and soggy.Not recommended ...

My family's go-to zichar place as it's within walking distance and is better than the other one near our home. Prawn paste chicken and xo pork ribs are our favourites. The saut√©ed broccoli with garlic is also just nicely done, not undercooked or overcooked. Love their San lau horfun, too. Fried rice is quite good, so is their beef fried rice. Their fish slice fried rice wasn't good though with slightly cold fish slices like it was cooked beforehand, put into the fridge, and then just thrown in with the fried rice when the rice was done. Their chicken fried rice was also not so good with pieces of chicken that was hard.
CKT is quite decent. Laksa is good,  pineapple and cucumber are thinly sliced BUT THE ONIONS ARE SO CHUNCKY and you could cry even by looking at them.

There are few places that have fish head steamboat. Of these few places there are even lesser that do not use msg. Here, the soup is without msg but taste good due to the quality of the stock used. Recommended if you love fish and non msg

I liked this restaurant for the good food.  They are very well prepared and delicious.  However,  when I was there with my family 2 weeks ago,  it was super crowded and noisy.  Too many families having birthday celebrations and moving around making it hard to hold our conversations.

Food: 4/5
Service: 4/5
Ambience: 3-4/5

As a fast food eatery, I expected bland food and uncaring staff. I received a welcome surprise though. The food was quite delectable, perfect for quick snacks, and the service was quick and quite affable. Overall, a great experience.
Have been buying salad from here. Their rice are delicious with generous serving:) very affordable pricing! Service is very good and the staffs are polite.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Service was far better than Jumbo. Quality of food very tasty n fresh.. Really a hidden gem in a Teochew club. Zui Teochew Cuisine should be very good too. All super yummy food.
Staff are candid in their recommendations. Food are tasty, even the old folks like it. I guess they have the Âè§ËÄÅÂë≥Ôºåreminiscing the old style zhi char taste I am used to in my childhood.
Amazing North Indian cuisine at an affordable price, staff are very friendly towards customers. 5/5 would recommend!
Worst attitute the staffs over here. All staffs should have name tags so will be easier to name them out on their lousy attitute. Please put a nametag on each staffs for easier complaint.
Tried their non spicy version - loved it!

restaurant name: Bangkok Street Mookata - Lor 8 Toa Payoh
content: Nice ambiance to enjoy mookata.
Delicious and good service . New outlet. Need to come early and queue up. üòä

Came here because of the good reviews. Ordered a sirloin steak. Worst steak I ever had. Cooked by a Chinese man. I asked for medium rare. He gave me well done. When i tried to return the steak, he told me medium rare and medium well are the same. Steak was terribly tough. Black pepper sauce absolutely tasteless. The only saving grace was crispy fries and good portion of coleslaw. It was a nightmare. I ended up throwing half the steak and just eating fries and coleslaw for dinner.

Many have commented their prices are above the norm, why not they just display their prices openly, so patron is able to know what they are expected to pay instead of getting surprises after they calculated the price. I have noticed having the same dishes on two visits but price are calculated differently... alamak üò¢

It was lunch for two at Din Tai Fung in Seletar Mall.  The steamed basket containing 5 pieces of xiao long bao was an upset. The bao and minced pork within has shrunk in size and content to a small dollop of 4cm diameter easily gulped down in one mouthful. The noodles with sliced mushrooms was also an upset. It was soggy with soy sauce. The only salvos were the fried rice and pickled cucumber.
Didn't bother to take photos.
Nice clean place for my sushi cravings. Order food by scanning the QR code and it's fun having to see your food arrive by the conveyer train. Prices are affordable and lots of options on their menu.
Hiked price and taste nothing great.Chapati were not even cooked properly..looks like new guys took over.not same as before ...but old aunty who serve food still there

Food is delicious and
Staff is friendly

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: Good. Eclectic. Relatively reasonable.

Your friendly neighbourhood Japanese eatery that's oozing with simplicity and charm. Don't expect any fancy games, it's just pure straight home cooked style Japanese food that's decent and economical. 98% of the dishes in the menu are below $20. Can't get better value that that surely, especially when this is not one of your usual hawker stall.
Again, the food's quality is decent and service is good too. Believe it or not , the chef cooking your Japanese meal is actually an Indian chap (see pict). How diverse and inclusive is that! üòÅüòã 3.5 stars.
Life-saver food shop for students as it opens late at night. Always crowded, sometime they serve the wrong order, make your to check before grabbing your to-go food.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: Best fish soup in town. Fish is big and the soup base is tasty .

Service was excellent!

Dishes tried:
XO fried rice - very good!
XO French bean - delicious!
Marmite chicken - fried chicken with marmite sauce, not bad.
Claypot eggplant - oily, generous with minced meat. Eggplant was soft. Not so good.
3 squares of meat with nacho cheese sauce and cheap burger bun for $5

Surprise find in a very quiet part of AMK. The mushroom soup & toast was comfort food after a long day, while the meat platter & sides are good to feed a hungry bunch üòä. Will be back to try the other beef items.

it has good cost-performance!
It tastes good!

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Would have given 5 stars but because of the very unfriendly and grumpy lady boss. Having a queue should bring joy rather than frustrations??? Your layout needs to be improved for better customer flow
The food is above average and very affordable.
The staff were surprisingly much more friendly

Pretty good grilled meat rice bowl. The egg was very well prepared, the yolk soft but not runny. The grilled meat was well grilled and seasoned.

Would definitely eat again.

The $4 add on for a vegetable skewer and a cup of roasted barley tea is a bit too pricy in my opinion. Mainly because both those add ons were pretty small. But if that's what it takes to keep the stall afloat, I guess I'll keep supporting.

The Tasha Murtabak is a huge portion with loads of ingredients inside such as chicken, cheese, capsicum, mushrooms and others. We tried the chicken bryani, limau O and tasha's teh. Highly recommended as well. The staff are friendly and warm!! Homey feels.

Nice Cantonese cuisine and also dim sum dishes available. Good soups plus 3 types meat available - steam chicken, roast pork, Barbeque pork! Noodles were also tasty n done el dente. Can be quite crowded during peak n may have to wait for a table. Many weekly offers available n also member discounts.

The worst customer experience ever! They ask you join the queue to order. After order, the system allowed you to order and pay. You will be asked to wait outside under the hot sun. After waiting for so long, they will tell you out of stock and refund you. So you basically queue to get refund of your own money! Such a waste of time! Staffs are rude too!
1st visit to the stall, tried pork chop (not much western food sells pork chop). It was tender and juicy. Great taste.

Joy the bandwagon to try why this one always have a long queue.  We waited for more than 1 hour to get a 3 pax table.  We ordered 3 sets with Wagyu steak, harami, beef steak slice, ox tongue, karubi and premium karubi.  The Wagyu beef is disappointing, not tender enough and also not strong enough for the fatty fragrance (already can tell from the marble pattern).  The beef steak slice is very dry.  The harumin is ok, tender and tends to be a bit chewy (but is ok).  The karubi is very good.  Ox tongue is extremely tender.  Last the stove is not coal but gas.  And the sauces are good - the Like BBQ and Salty sauce.  Overall it is not exception ally good but is definitely value for money, especially for the lower price point items - karubi.  Worth to try.  Last last last, why can't the queuing system can ask the customer to input HP number and can send SMS to us like 5 tables ahead?  This is a very common feature is many systems.

The food is good. But the service is not good. If there any delay in serving food then they should inform earlier while placing the order rather than keep us waiting for 45mins. All are busy in packing the food for online orders only.
Great chinese food

Service has improved tremendously! Manager and staff were very polite and helpful. This is a huge improvement from the previous team of staff. I‚Äôd rate the service 5 üåüüåüüåüüåüüåü

I can‚Äôt say the same for the food quality. The pratas were average, just soft and there‚Äôs zero crisps (not even on the outside). Plaster prata came with a fully cooked egg. Garlic nann was extremely tough as well. Teh was poorly made.
The aunty serving was friendly and the food was big in portions, worth the money spent.

Visited during lunch time on Saturday, restaurant was about half filled, staff were warm and friendly. Food were good but nothing spectacular, price was reasonable for most of the menu. Great place for gathering as their table can be easily rearrange for more seatings of 10 pax easily and wasn't too noisy for chatting.

Being a secondary school alumni of this location, our group of ex-classmates will always try out the establishment at this location (which has gone through several changes over the years). This time, the Malayan Council i hope can last longer as it was the most crowded as compared with previous few establishments.
They served what i think was malaysian/indonesian fusion food. I had the more classic tahu telor as was quite full that day and my mates had the warm avocado salad, sambal goreng pasta and seafood tanghoon. Overall, service was good and prompt, nice ambience too. Food though, i find it average at best, maybe caused we had high expectations to start with. Hope they continue to improve on their offering.

Surprising ok. Look, the ingredients are not top quality, the short grain rice is not the expensive Japanese brand, but this is a hawker stall selling Japanese meals at $5. I give it 4 stars for doing what it is doing with this budget.

Had the teriyaki chicken don. The chicken taste a bit like western chicken chop, but it was pretty good size. The overall taste is conservative, maybe because of the neighborhood taste.

Will come back to try other items.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Tasty food and good service! A bit pricey.

The meat here is AMAZING!!! So well marinated and tender. The mookata here is so affordable and came to about $10/pax and I ate till I was so full. In terms of value for money, taste and service speed, its a full 5 stars. In fact, the only reason why I dont have a photo is because the food was so delicious everything was gone in my tummy alr haha

I have been here many time. Friendly staffs with good service. Their congee ho jiak, the gong pao liver also tok kong! Best dish to go with the plain congee and you tiao. The chicken feet was so yummy that I can eat non stop.

Rarely post reviews but I feel that I have to, after dining here. We had the Gyu dons and also the pork version. Meats were grilled perfectly with a hint of charcoal taste. Crispy and very lightly burnt. Poached eggs were perfect, too. Prices were very reasonable and portions considered generous. Unless you are a big eater. The only downside was the waiting time. Please expect 15 minutes or more as food is prepared freshly. We were there without a queue and had to wait 15 minutes. If you are in a rush or with low patience, this is not for you.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content: We tried Pepper Mutton, Pomfret fry, Chicken Masala & few others and all were great

I ordered pork belly. This shop really love up to their name, the pork belly actually had slight tinge of charred flavour and the fats of the pork belly is well rendered. They are also generous with the side dish. The price was ONLY $9.90 Definitely willing to try again. Regretted that I didn't order the other stuff there.

Held my wedding dinner at Jubilee Garden Restaurant. Torrence and Banquet Manager Kent were very prompt in their replies. They guided us through the procession and the program, constantly assuring us that things will turn out well. They were also very helpful, polite and generous.

The food was delicious and value for money. Portions were big and our guests loved the food.  Thank you so much for making our wedding dinner such a special one. Greatly appreciated.

(Photos featured were taken during our food tasting session.)
Food n service  good üëç

It's full house on a Saturday evening and it's a long wait for the dishes to be out. Food is nice generally but some aren't that great. The yam paste dessert isn't smooth enough. The steam fish is slightly overcooked.
Impressed by the food quality and the service provided! Value for money and worth it! However, there‚Äôs a few flies which quite annoys me during the dine.

restaurant name: Wee Nam Kee Hainanese Chicken Rice Restaurant
content: Portion is pathetic. Was given a few scraps of meat that look like leftovers from an unfinished meal.  Whats more despicable, is the raising of price without updating their menu price or informing customer (due to chicken shortage so they claimed). So disappointed as i used to frequent them in the past, but food is now mediocre with questionable bussiness practices.

Went to have the meal slight earlier than normal meal time can avoid the crowd or Long queue wait. The staff was attentive to customer and friendly during their service. Food are fresh and delicious. Serving if the food was fast to the order. Green tea was on refillable and they taste nicely.

restaurant name: Hwang Sil Jjajang Jjampong specialty restaurant
content:
Safety Warning!
Foods were good, but their chairs were broken yet they decided still to use them (multiple broken chairs), which caused blackspot bruise injury to my index finger immediately. When I asked why they did not remove the broken chairs, they said, ‚Äúno choice as we are still waiting for the new supply. The owner knows about it‚Äù  When I asked again if there was any one injured before, surprisingly yes there was‚Ä¶ they rather prefer to get customers hurt.. just be careful‚Ä¶ you can be the next person with bruise or even worse injuries.

We were charged $4.50 for a piece of paru (lungs) inside the rojak. Gravy is tasty.

We hope you can be more practical on the pricings. Your pricing board says depends on size without even weighing the items. You do not practise offering customers a receipt for their purchase.

The service is very bad. My queue number was called but have to wait for 5+mins for me to enter. The workers messed up my order and l waited for 40mins until l called them to check my order. They were chi chatting and don‚Äôt even care about the customers. Very bad service. Will never go again.

Terrible arrival to hear that they didn't recurs your dinner bookings for 7. And there was a long line of angry customers waiting to walk in. There is only one mgr looking lady. But she's not manning the reservation. She's was also taking orders from customers seated already. Asked the other junior staff and they just ignore and indicated it was not their responsibility.

The owner should relook at how they allocate staff appropriately.

After dinner, I have to queue to pay and that takes another 20min in the queue.

I will never come back. Period.
This is third time come, everytime come the standard is there, food are very nice , the price also reasonable üëçüèºüòã
chicken tikka pasta was great and must try.after I ordered we got the food in 3 minutes. my food was received  dry hot and yummy ‚Ä¶ must try this place as value for money

Update 27/9/2021 - The food standard has dropped a lot. Not sure what happened, did they change recipe or changed owners? The claypot rice, claypot sesame chicken and claypot klang BKT tastes totally different from 4 months ago.

Great tasting food but some of the staff here are seriously rude to another level. Foods here taste somewhat like Malaysia and the prices and portions are very reasonable.

Three stars because of the staff‚Äôs attitude. Very conveniently located near the Farrer Park MRT (Purple Line). One can expect to spend less than $20 for 3 claypot dishes and 2 drinks.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content:
Good customer service, but i ordered indian full grilled chicken  its not same in indian style totally different. They add after the owen some masalas and red chilli, the masala raw smell. I want tamilnadu restaurants style crispy and dry and fully cookied  grilled chicken from owen.  Please take note.. Next time give me..
Thank you so much
Normal rojak but i like the tek terak
Extremely good atmosphere, delicious food and beers, and very sociable + attentive staff / boss.
Fantastic food and we especially love the chilli chicken signature dish. Such a friendly restaurant run by a family. About $12 per dish which will feed 2 if u order rice.

5 Stars if you order both types of ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖ.
Four stars for all the other types of food except for noodles which I've yet to try.
It's authentic but the QC leaves some room for improvement.
Overall I still gave five stars because the price is very affordable!

restaurant name: Sushi Express Take Out @ Toa Payoh
content: I loved the corn sushi because they make it well and it is hard to find elsewhere and it was very reasonably priced but they stopped selling it for no reason at all. It was one of the best outlets I know but getting worse and worse. Would not go there ever again because no reason to

I ordered salmon steak from stall Chester Weston Grill noticed that the fish was not fully done or half raw. So I approached the person whom take my order for replacement. He was rude telling me that they don't check the entire piece of fish and claiming that if you want replacement then he will need to call his boss for approval first.

This stall is located at Jurong West Street 91.

The chicken, soup and toufu were tasty although on the pricey side. However, before the meal, i discovered a cockroach in my Pu Er tea. When we told the staff, we did not even get an apology. Well, you won‚Äôt see us back there anytime soon.
Interesting food and nicely plated. Recommended if you are interested to be delighted by innovative food that tastes good for a medium range price
The sushi was good
Chicken was quite nice and boneless, portion order was for 2 and it's delicious. Only problem is that the soup wasn't provided. Highly reccomend

Hi management would like to highlight an issue isit a rule that char kway teow must always fried with chilli? Your people got a lot of own rules that I think the management are not aware. The other time the jurong point char kway teow refused to sell me 2 plate as I only have a $50 note which later the jurong point management apologies that there is no such rule.  Please look into it
Food is delicious.. live seafood.. nice service. Will definitely go back again

Family comfort food! Good quality and reasonable priced.. famous for their fish slice noodle and kway teow dishes besides hei ko chicken wings etc.. had the curry fishhead which was fresh and meaty.. enjoy
This restaurant is a hidden gem. Their prata and noodle dishes are a must try

Favourite Hakka/Chinese restaurant to have a hearty satisfying meal. You better make reservations esp on weekends, if not arrive when they open and you might be lucky.
A must order is their Hakka Tofu and Preserved Veg with Braised Pork. I also tried their duck before and it was amazing. This place is well loved by my family, hubby and friends too!

First time being charge for extra bowl of curry!!!  This manager in the photos shouted $0.50 for extra curry !!! Environment is really dirty,, birds flying around eating food on the tables !!! Eat at your own risk!!!!!

Food taste good.  The prata is freshly made by order.  Expect to wait about 10 min or more after placing order.  Pricing slightly on the high side.  A simple meal costs approx $8-10 for 2 persons.  $2 for an egg prata.  The set meals looks more value for money. Though the place is usually crowded during meal times, the tables are cleared very quickly (even before my friend and I finished eating).  A little noisy here.  Need to raise my voice when placing my order and the number calling for your collection of prata buzzing loudly away.  My clothes smell of fried oil after dining in for less than 30 min.  Would recommend takeaway instead of dining in.
Quite a nice place. BBQ available for 1 person.. but this place need stronger aircon, sweat a lot after eating! Would be nice if they have more options for non-beef eater.

Was there yesterday afternoon with my customers. The service was fast and very polite. They have the warm and personal touch when ask for  recommendations of dishes. They know their menu very well. What food which page and even the ingredients. Well done. Will surely go again and support them.

Came here at 730pm on a Sunday evening.  Ordered the local favorites: rojak, popiah, longtong, oyster omelette.

Rojak was decent, slightly on the sweeter side.  The vegetables fruits like radish, cucumber, guava were fresh and crunchy.  The youtiao had a crunch as well. The pineapples were unripe.

Popiah was similar, since the sweet sauce was the same base, over powered the salty fragrance that the cooked radish would have provided.

Lontong was rich and tasty.  The saving grace for the meal.  The gravy had the right richness and taste that made you want to dig in more.  The Tau kwa was generous.  Portions were right for 1 pax.

Oyster omelette was the first to order and last to receive.  The cook on the starch was poor and "jelak".  The oysters over cooked and the chili was "off" with a rancid water taste.

By the time that we were done by 810, we wanted to order hot drinks, the man at the counter said. No more hot drinks.

Well, it's just sad.  I wouldn't encourage you to return, you are better off eating at the foodcourt.

As For Delivery Rider This Store Really Waste Our Time,Mostly Need To Wait The Early 30Mins And 45mins,Use To Wait For 2 Plain Prata And Briyani,I Have To Wait More Then 45Mins,And That Point Of Time The Store Not Busy Less Customer Dinning In,Seriously Name Srisun Express But Not That Express

Try the Xing Hua Beehoon and Lor mee! Definitely nicer than the other dishes. We ordered both medium size, $8. The lor mee is substantially a lot more and can probably be shared between 3 people while the beehoon can be shared between 2. The other dishes e.g. deep fried crispy prawn fritters $8 has no hint of prawns, just taste like regular Ngoh Hiang, and the stir fried white clams $10 with spicy sauce was very salty. There isn‚Äôt any queue when I went there on a weekday dinner.

Place is clean & service  consistence. Food portion just right & testy of course. But they use dettol as cleaning solution for table, leaving a strong disinfecting smell quite unpleasant. They can use odourless disinfecting solution. Just a suggestion.
Saltiest ma la i've eaten in my life
Great place!!
Ordered dry burning fish head and the dish was not even warm. Asked the staff to make it hot and ended up with a warm dish instead. Give up!
It is a pleasant experience as the service was good and the ambience was nice

1) Ala carte buffet with super long waiting time for your order.
2) Food portion small (Example 5pax = 5 prawns per order)
3) Bad customer services from manager to staffs
4) Totally not recommended
5) Totally waste people money and time
6) The worst restaurant ever been.
Old school western fare. Chicken cutlet is still good, chicken chop was too dry.
it's my one of the favourite restaurant food and drinks taste yummy amazing üëè üòã

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: We visited Ang Mo Kio Nandhana‚Äôs on the opening day. We ordered tomato soup, mutton soup and palak paneer with butter naan and spicy chicken noodles. Also we ordered tawa  fish fry and  for the dessert kulfi. The food was amazing and we really enjoyed eating it. We got the items on time and the service also was very good.
went last week and got a great service  Despite the peak hours was able to continuously help me with the countless refills of ginger and hot ocha.

Ordered salted egg crab on Nov 8 at past 10pm thru Foodpanda @ $50+ for a piece. The crab was depressing, I hardly ate any crab meat.  meat was mushy and solid, not firm and springy.  Meat was sticking to the shell, the main shell itself had nothing.  When your eatery/restaurant has "seafood" on it, pls live up to it!  The food that came is just $5 worth or less for the salted egg gravy which was so so.  I was scammed!
Impressed by almost every dish! üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüòãüòãüòã

Ordered their chicken and mushroom Alfredo, the chicken tasted "old" and hard.

Guess this should be remove from menu

Update: wrote a 5 star review but husband and I subsequently got terrible abdominal pain and diarrhea in the middle of the night after eating dinner here!! Signals that their hygiene level is not up to standard! Will not patronise again, unfortunately.

===========

Very unassuming place, in an industrial building.

Pleasantly surprised by the food. The curry is really thick and flavourful. The curry chee cheong fun was amazing. The plain CCF with spring onion was decent too.

Curry mee was nice with a lot of ingredients. Ipoh curry hor fun was nice too, quite different in flavour.

Overall great, just wish it wasn't so oily. The food is pretty "sinful", won't eat so often but will be back.

Horrible experience ! Cockroaches in the restaurant.
My mum had been there previously and the food was good. But had a horrible experience today. There were small cockroaches running around the place. Spotted at least 3 of them. To make matters worse, one of their staff (Imran) was extremely rude. His exact words were ‚Äúcockroaches are everywhere‚Äù implying that it‚Äôs normal to have cockroaches in a F&B establishment and continued to argue that the place is clean. He did not take any accountability whatsoever and had the cheek to argue that it‚Äôs not a big deal to have cockroaches running around in a restaurant. The manager then spoke to me to address the issue. He was very nice and polite but it doesn‚Äôt make a difference that the restaurant is infested with small cockroaches. I will not be returning to this place ever again.
Horfun taste good as usual but I saw a small little worm in my horfun 4 days ago. Was it from the vegetables?
Not bad buffet spread! But note that there are additional charges on drinks and starters!

Nice dining experience.
Food served was fresh and nice üëç
so expensive despite being in campus.
a nice hearty pasta! it was very filling and tasted very good. the service was also wonderful here.
Pretty good food wish there was more salt. Will drop by if I ever pass by again.

This is the most authentic mapo doufu I have tasted in singapore. However, The Peking duck is rather bland and the skin is not even crispy. The only highlight of the duck dish is the sauce and the wrap which are both made by the chef delicately. I think Singapore does not have the real Peking ducks to be purchased.
Best value set meal

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Not worth the price you pay. Very little choices. The price you pay for buffert does not include drinks or dessert which is not interesting at all (pay seperately). Will not come again.
Missing order. Bad queue and order management. ‚òπÔ∏è Staff are nice though.

Food taste is so good permeate the stomach that increase one's appetite.  Chef has excellent culinary skills which draw the best favour out of each dish and the sauces greatly enhanced the natural taste of seafood and meats.  The chilli sauce is a must try and unforgettable.

restaurant name: Siam Square Mookata - Best Mookata Restaurant in Singapore
content: Portion was just nice. Price was OK to me.
Although abit on the pricey side (could do w abit more quantity), their baked pasta is one of the best ones you can find in school!! really friendly staff too :D

Ordered set on the menu. It was quite filling for lunch. Quite a big portion for the rice and the meat.
It was delicious üòãü§§

We were seated at outdoor, it wasn't hot but quite windy. But getting/calling the staff from outdoor was difficult.

Lunch hour wasn't that pack for this restaurant.

prata is pretty good and decent BUT the MILO TOWER IS A MUST AVOID. You would expect to get $13 dollars worth of milo but nope‚Ä¶the canister inside the tower thts supposed to separare the ice frm the milo isnt used, hence they pour the milo and the ice in the same compartment. Meaning tht your milo is going to get watered down AF. Its not like the milo is alrdy thick and the ice will thin it down. I tried it the second the milo was on my table and I knew the ice was gonna ruin the drink. Look at my photos

was quite expensive even for kosong prata. If im not wrong their egg and onion is like $3 but its ok i guess
The couple chef is very cute and the food is priced even cheaper than normal zi char. Everything is around 5-7 for staples and less than 25 for fish. Tasty, good service and cosy

Late lunch after 2pm on a public holiday, no queue. Scan menu to order. Like the ability to add salad $2 to the dons which come with miso soup (seaweed, tofu & clams). The 3 kinds buta jyu $23 bbq pork - good flavourful fats and the wagyu suji don - tender beef stew $18.90 were the preferred ones. Wagyu stamina Don - grilled beef $23.90 was ok too but a little tougher...
Big portion. Good service. Can Bring 2 containers for take away to save 20 cents.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content:
Went there during lunch hour. The queue moves very fast and they‚Äôll reserve tables specially for bigger groups.

The teh tarik is a must try.

Can‚Äôt wait to come back to try more dishes.
Good prata and spicy curry
My best happy food...

Spoilt for choice and decided to try the Konoha sannin experience/set.
Food is great and very laid back casual dining.
Our server deserves mention.
Michelle is very patient and accommodating. She definitely contributed to the overall pleasant experience

The pork chop is hard... Not soft and tender as the king of fried rice..

The only flavorful is the rice has strong smoky charcoal taste.

Overall, I rather go for king.

restaurant name: Hua Zai HK Style Roasted Delight Rice Noodle
content: Food is good, but cleaniness is the key to everything in food. Found a plastic in my packed food. Not sure, if I am going back.

The total cost of all the items here cost $30, the noodles are $10 and $6, while the side cost $4-5. The reason I'm giving 3 stars is not because the noodles are bad. Oh no, the reason for this is because the gyoza is overcooked and from the photo, you can see for yourself.

How could the staff send out food like this.
Always great. Always consistent. Super fats service. I recommend the spicy noodles, rice with egg and pork, spicy wonton, hot and sour soup, duck in crispy spring onion pastry

No problem with parking, ambience is good, nice and quiet surroundings. We came during the fasting time and we were the only table for lunch. Main courses are big portion. Perhaps for the barramundi dish can improve on the presentation. The mushroom sauce is similar to the mushroom soup in taste and texture. Liked the ondeh cake as u can can bite the bits of gula melaka within. Pizza crust is biscuit like texture.

restaurant name: Chui Huay Lim Teochew Cuisine ÈÜâËä±ÊûóÂìÅÊΩÆËΩ©
content: Quite a nice place to bring my old folks here. Good restaurants and good wedding halls
Very nice traditional japanese food and traditional setting out
Nice food

After visiting a few loklok stalls, I still come back to this stall! This is really the best LOKLOK stall for me. The food was fried at the right temperature and duration! After a long day, this is my comfort food.
Lovely food , only down side is that the place is very tiny.  Had to squeeze when someone walks past

Overpriced for $11 bucks food
Will not recommend not very clean and their air freshener is right on top on diners. Auto Spray all over u!
Just ate lunch over there not bad chicken randang but I miss something in it hmmm it's ok anyway nice taste

never again, the rice is just as bad as described by others and the raw fish wasn't fresh. hope I don't get food poisoning

if the owner/franchisee owner sees this. like seriously send your chef for rice cooking lesson.

your rice is seriously a disgrace and burning all the effort of the rice farmer. literally unedible.

the rice is mushy, sticky and dry at the same time.

waiter responded exactly as described by others with the blur look of huh really ah

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Great food, suggest coming on weekend to try the seeraga samba rice. The malasa tea was a little too sweet for my taste buds but everything else was great
The mermaid collagen soup is rich in taste and  excellent. Must try .
Great location in middle of the school campus, able to customise and pasta was made on the spot, good service too!! Will patronise againü´∂üèª
Good authentic chicken rice. I like the ambience and the crew too.
Along the road, good food but limited variety, service a bit poor
Came here with company for CNY lunch. Buffet style. Not bad. Their service is good. Food tastes not bad. Price is affordable too. Will be back again another time.
Food is good...taste is good...price is reasonable...cooks very fast upon order.

Good food with a little home taste. Try the braised beef $15.90 sharing portion. Haybee hiam bun $1.50 is excellent. Generous filling. Note this is halal restaurant. Strictly no "outside" food allowed. You may not eat your own birthday cake there.

Understandable.

most of the dishes are good üëçüèæüëçüèæüëçüèæüòãüòãüòãüëçüèæüëçüèæüëçüèæ
my personal must order dishes are deep fried seabass fillet, pork in spur sauce, pork cheek, deep fried pork w garlic, stir fried chicken w garlic, tomyam creamy, brinjal and lime juice.
I tried the mama fried basil noodles, it's like Thai version of Maggi goreng. Portions are pretty good.

Servicewise, still excellant. However,their samsui chicken is now very tasteless and texture is just wrong. Not half as addictive as before and i lost interest completely after eating the 2nd piece..even dunking it in the ginger sauce didnt help any.
The medium size ah por fan shu vegetable was very small in portion as well,and was limpid and bland tasting..
Their specialty hometown tofu had no special taste nor texture to it,and their fish slices with ginger were insipid and tasteless.
My all time favourite of olive fried rice was clumpy and yet superbly oily.
I have been a long time fan of their brand but i m beginning to think if i should revisit and revise this fact.
Paid quite a lot for this bill and yet went away feeling pretty shortchanged and disillusioned with the meal.

I would like to compliment A very kind and friendly staff of yours, Mr Alan!

He never fails to greet us every time we visit. In fact, he took the effort to remember us!

Kudos to such an awesome worker of yours. üëç

Worst service ever. Clearly stated on shop it opens at 830am, at 840am, we knocked on the closed shutter, 3 times female staff didn't respond, on 4th time, she came out and scolded us to not knock on the shutter and tell us its not open yet. Clearly if opening time is 830, the stall should have been opened already. Yet From this bad attitude, can tell why this stall doesn't have alot of customers during lunch crowd.
Nice and delicious Mango Salad that i eat ever

Homely food, friendly owner, great prices! Love their very reasonably priced teishoku sets which allows me to savour so many things at once - on top of the main item of your choice, you also get nikujaga (my comfort food!), potato salad, ebi fry, gyoza, chicken karaage, edamame. Only downside is limited parking spaces nearby during peak periods.
Excellent place for Lunch ‚òïÔ∏èüëçüèº
The roast duck is awesome. Their main dishes are pretty good too. The dim sum though, is just average for a higher tier restaurant such as this. I don‚Äôt mind returning for their roast meat.

restaurant name: Al Mubin Restaurant - Ang Mo Kio
content: One of the staff give attitude just because we wanted to order more for the same dish. Not to mention, when the staff said that he would get back to us whether or not the dish still available, they didn't even care. So we went to ask the same staff, he still dares to roll his eyes at us. But food is good just that staff.

Very yummy, reasonable prices. Try the salt / pepper fried squid. Light and tasty and squid was tender. The homemade tofu with enoki mushroom was also a gem.

We came early for dinner (about 545pm) and food was served within 10 mins - very fast!

Recommended.
Very good Ribs and grilled chicken. Buddy gave us 2 small potatoes without us asking, so that we can share. Nice touch! üòã
Delicious tomato soup

Just had late lunch due to the nearby hawker centre being closed for a few days.

Standard of food is about same as those sold in mrt stations. But at a different price point.

2 stars for the black pepper chicken rice. The soup was as salty as sea water. The quarter chicken was refried to a shade darker than fast food chicken, and then tossed with the black pepper sauce.

3 stars as the ice coffee saved the meal.

Food is good , place is cosy for chats and lay backs. Only service is severely lacking as workers are more keen in chatting among themselves than paying attention to diners who wants to order despite a not crowded weekend night.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content:
Yam Cake ($20) ‚Ä¢ First time having this dish. Not a fan of yam but I really enjoyed this dish. There were fresh prawns pea cashews and a lot of mushrooms.

San Lou Hor Fun ($12) ‚Ä¢ We revisited this place because the previous we were here everyone ordered this dish and it looked so good. But sadly, it wasn‚Äôt up to expectations..the one at Upper Thomson had a better texture and more gravy.

#letsguide #burpple #foreverhungry #singaporeeats #instagood #chope #hungryeatwhat #hungryeatwhere #foodie #foodiesg #hungrygowhere #chope #entertainerapp #sgfood

The wagyu beef truffle Hor fun ‚Ä¶ is a must have . The meal was tasty . Also had the braised red Garoupa fish soup with pickled cabbage and chilli . Fish was fresh and soup was good and a tad spicy . Bakes bacon salad Delicious but pricy . Overall I would come back again . Staff was very friendly and ambience was welcoming .

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content:
Very disappointed with their food and service, the reviews wrote till so‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.
Seriously I won‚Äôt be coming back. Period
The famous s11 western food at amk central 711 is here at 347. Came to have a quick dinner. Taste still about same. And maybe due to cost cutting measures, portions have decreased.
Juicy tender chicken chop! Amazing! Fries were a little over fried tho.
Good ambience. Food was delicious and price range is match with what they served.

Bak Chang. Saw a writeup.
Called v early around 10am. Cust service was great and helpful. Ordered to collect.
Restaurant was busy at 11.30am when opened.
Staff pleasant. We split bills.

Back Chang with scallops was very good for the price point. Taste was v good. Not oily. Not jilark.

Will definitely buy again.

And will try to eat when circuit breaker is off

This is our family must have for big or small occasion for past 40yrs. Birthdays, public holidays, festive season - u name it. If anyone is on annual leave on particular day, "anyone" wil volunteer to go pack this for everyone. Sorely missed when out if Sg. This is how good they are. Consistently flavourful. Taste like home, warms our hearts.

Don‚Äôt want to splurge but looking for a decent Japanese meal? Can try this quaint cafe that serves a filling and quick meal to satisfy craving. Decent price point for average food served in the basement of Westgate. Recommend to try their beef and pork belly bowls. Each meal comes with a light rice tea to cleanse the palette.
Fun
Waitress are all very friendly, food taste good too!
Nice cosy ambience no crowd on sat morning, thosai served was burnt on the sides.. Service can be improved, prices are very modest... Manager a young man not so friendly and helpful.
The service and the food was excellent especially Mr Vijay best Customer service,  he recommends best sellers and cheerful guy
Amazing restaurant, great food and friendly staff.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: 5 of us came on a weekday in the early afternoon where we were the only ones at the restaurant. We ordered fish and chips that came 40mins later. We were overcharged for the drinks and wasn‚Äôt told of the ‚Äúnew‚Äù price until we received the ‚Ä¶

restaurant name: Hom Aroy Thai Food Express (TOA PAYOH LORONG 7)
content: I always order delivery by Grab. And always same items Mango Salad, Basil Pork Rice and Pad Thai. Food delivered hot and my favourite is Pad Thai. Comes with 3 prawns n egg fried inside the dish. Mango salad well cut and I like the half spicy n tangy taste!! Yummy always!!

I think this is one of the worst review I‚Äôve given but I still wana give them 2 star to encourage the owner to keep improving. Firstly they have a very wide range of food choices on the menu. And seems like an authentic Japanese restaurant‚Ä¶ but very disappointed after you try them. The cha Siew ramen tasted exactly like an instant noodle powder soup base. Noodle are not fresh either. Sushi platter was the worst. Salmon Harumaki came very tiny and badly made. They didn‚Äôt give me the tamago maki as checked with the chef and said it was out of stock. Cucumber maki was bitter. Pumpkin croquette was ok as it is deep fried before serving. It‚Äôs basically food court standards but restaurant pricing.
Prompt service & helpful staff. Fresh ingredients & yummylicious soups.
Cheong fan texture is nice but too dry, curry is thick but the spice taste is too strong like hindu curry. Á¥îÂ±¨ÂÄã‰∫∫Âè£Âë≥

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Good value ala carte lunch buffet. The service by the staff was good and fast.
Have Been Wanted To Try For Awhile, Finally... Visited üòä I Think It's Much Better Than Sushi Express & Similar To Genki Sushi üòãüëç Will Be Back~

Im really fussy when comes to food..
And i came here to try for the first time.. i heard is nice.. üòè i dont need to comment much but ill give more than 5 stars!! Absolutely wow! Truffle mushroom soup, im dying for that!!ü•∞

But wait, my husband waited for his food for an hr.
Yes their waiting time is damn slow. Not enough manpower to serve outdoor customers.

Get to know the chef missed out his order.. kinda sad but luckily my dish portion is quite big so i shared with him.. hope it wont repeat the same thing to others..

Good food and pet friendly. Will visit again
Not bad for a 3 week old cafe üôÇ

Update:
Went back on their 4th week of business with more friends. Waiting time improved.

restaurant name: Hong Kong Street Chun Tat Kee 881 (XO) Fish Head Beehoon
content: The hor fun was passable. The salted egg sotong did not look so authentic but turned out to be not bad. Wanted to try the crab beehoon and found it too expensive for 2 pax.

Call if a stroke of bad luck when most of the reviews I'm reading are positive. My food was terrible. My beef was done to medium when I requested for medium rare. The curly truffle fries were over fried, something I never expected any establishments to get wrong, especially one that has been around for the longest time. The iced lemon tea was sweet beyond honey.

The only 2 that were good and edible were the slab of salmon and the ice cream, which I believe is outsourced.

Staff were a hit and miss. Some were extremely polite and hospitable, while some just ignored you like you're transparent.

Not returning for sure.

It serves the best white chicken in heartland restaurants that I've eaten. The chicken was tender & juicy. Next is the sweet & sour fish. Very well seasoned & the taste is just right, served hot coming straight from the kitchen. Worth going there again.
Yummy food and chilled out interior! But takes too long to serve food.
Nearby stall to quench thirst of ramen. Not on par as the resto. But this is on a different level compares with fishball noodle.

First and last time here, I don‚Äôt usually write reviews but I Ordered teriyaki chicken don cause I saw that it was the chef‚Äôs recommendation. For $7.80 plus service charge and GST, you are getting mushy clumped up rice and tasteless chicken. If I am being brutally honest, the food in army cookhouses taste better. Better off patronising the Japanese store in the food court.

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: Happy to have a good Indian Restaurant at Ang Mo Kio.
Extremely good atmosphere, delicious food and very sociable + attentive staff especially Ashton.
Always closed

One of the best ribeye steaks from a local western coffee shop stall one can find, grilled to your preferred doneness. Mine came medium, succulent and moist, and at $16.80, that‚Äôs pretty good value. Staff is friendly too.
I felt the good hospitality of Mr Mahendran and Mdm Meena. And excellent customer service staff's. They served their customer with courtesy.

Overpriced experienced
Roast duck and char Siew for two persons is $16. Just Noodles alone is $2 per plate. While the duck taste good but too overpriced.
Freshly made sushi served by cute robots in many expressions. A good variety of sushi at affordable prices. Very satisfied meal, will be back for more!
All side dishes are cold

I live in the neighborhood near this restaurant and there are many thai places near by. Out of all, i think this one is the best one in terms of the authenticity of food, quality of service. The staffs here are so attentive and explain to you about menu very kindly.  Super Thai is a really nice place to dine in as well as to quickly pick up (they prepare it very fast) and bring home to eat.

They also have a super value lunch sets on the weekdays,  which makes my wfh lunch time very satisfying. Their chicken wings are to die for lol.

When i have home gathering, this food never went wrong.

Hidden within the industrial estate, an Ipoh eatery that serves very nice Malaysian food. Various style of Chee Chiong Fun not the type you find in hawker. Like the CCF mushroom & meat, nasi lemak, Rojak (with added crackers), and curry noodles.

Tried their chicken Murtabak, it was quite disappointing. At the first look, it seems good, but when I tried the first bite, it was tasteless and the flour is soggy, not crispy as all. The chicken meat was bland, and it breaks up into pieces easily. At the price of $7.00, I do not think it was worth it.

Stall owner is friendly & accommodating to order request
Loves the Longtong as it's fresh cabbage and ingredients well cooked with lemak definitely a go for dish
Briyani with long grain rice with spicy Chicken curry just appetizing with extra curry and papadan, a filling meal indeed. But must note that this is different from Indian Briyani

Will go back for more and update with Photos of dishes üòâ

Passby here so went in to check it out n surprisingly the pineapple rice was really delicious! I definitely would go back for their pineapple rice again. One dish I wont order again is the soup, we find the soup tastes too plain. For these dishes plus 2 drinks total was $50. ‚ò∫Ô∏è
All the ingredients are fresh...Nice Nasi Lemak and just for the price of $3

Properly one of the best Spicy Sichuan Frog leg.
My favourites. Really very good and spicy.

Brought my mum to celebrate Mother‚Äôs Day at Tori Yard. While the food is on the pricier side, as per all Japanese restaurant, the quality of food is worth the price. The cold soba was surprisingly good (my guess it‚Äôs handmade due to uneven strands of noodle). The sashimi is fresh and thick cut too. The waiter forgot our sushi order, so we waited quite a while. We were pleasantly surprised when he served us free cups of tea for keeping us waiting. Unfortunately the sushi was abit underwhelming. While it tasted not bad but we preferred the traditional kind as compared to this new creation that has a crisp batter. Overall, it‚Äôs a nice place to catch up with delicious food.

Food was average. Had the tom yum soup, basil chicken and glass noodles with prawn. Nothing memorable and lemongrass drink doesnt even have the lemongrass taste. Though price is relatively affordable but there are several other affordable places with better tasting thai food. The staff, this local girl was friendly and nice but thai lad( shld b the boss) was quite arrogant and rude. We wanted to take away 2 dishes as we couldnt finish, staff was kind to suggest she will pack separately but charge us 30c, but eventually the boss insisted that we shld be charged 60c. We r fine to pay cos it wss the staff that made the suggestion in the first place, but eventually 1 of the boxes wasnt even a proper box but a more flimsy plastic. If u wanna charge have thr decency to give a proper box. boxes need to be paid for in cash as well.
Sumptuous vegetarian food. Had the chicken rice, nasi lemak and the buttered abalone mushroom. Chef puts a lot of effort in gettimg the taste right. Recommended.

Went there after watching the amk fireworks for national day.
Not the best place for service or food..
If an Indian Muslim place can't get the parata right, it's definitely a place to avoid.
The service us very slow, no staff to take the order I had to chase the cook to take my order directly.

They are so understaffed that you could walk away without paying a dime.

Had one of the most disappointing experience at Jack's Place. I grew up eating JP and I will always remember its great service and food, but today's experience tainted the image of JP.

We ordered their triple meat grill and the meat(doneness was great) but the pasta was way undercooked. The manager on the ground was quick to resolve my unhappiness but in return, I still received undercooked pasta with some mushroom sauce(not sure if their pasta was microwaved).

Understanding that drink and dessert will be served after your main course. Only our dessert arrived and we did not receive our drink at all (suspect that they forgot about it). When we rectified at the counter, they apologized and offered us can drink instead which we declined.

I can empathise with it lack of manpower(as I used to work in an F&B outlet), but at least remember your customer's order and delivered it on time when requested.

Kudos to the manager who hears my feedback, but I'm still taken a back by today's experience.

Ridiculous place. Waited 30 minutes for 2 prata to be told they have no prata. There are also alot of birds flying into this establishment. There is an alternative springleaf prata just across the street at safra.

In many of the patrons review shop was told to contact their whatsapp number. That's not necessary cos I'm not coming back again.

Authentic Malaysian hawker food, but small portion and a bit pricey compared with Malaysia boleh. I had the Assam laksa, the soup was quite watery with less than minimum fish meat. I also ordered one lok bak to try, it's so tiny with $2 each. I prefer Malaysia boleh.

So lucky to be walking by and noticing a zero wait time.

Ordered the Quattro set as well as extra beef tongue and short ribs.

The staff are young and some are obviously new but you can tell they are trying their best at service.

So give them a smile and they would appreciate it!

The rice was the only thing that I would pick on as it seems a tad too mushy for our liking.

Bad service.. they're trying to control your food intake knowing that it's a buffet hotpot.
Reason from them: no pending orders,  but paper was handed over to the staff.

Tips:
Sit inside if you want good service, bad service, sit outside..
They're passing around some satays etc.. if  you are inside..
Ask for the ice cream and fruits, it's free flow but they won't tell you and didn't inform us.
It's getting more n more pricy .... Ordered beef rendang ... Potato ... N curry vege $7 ...ü§™

restaurant name: Lark Lark Mookata - GARDEN by the BEER
content: Good beer selection, open air environment,  good food as well

It's a place where you cab rely on when you need some comfort food like the Siao Long Pau or the Ramen. The quality has been consistent and there isnt too many varieties to confuse you. Price is on rhe high side if comparinf to hawker food
Affordable and delicious!

restaurant name: Nandhana's @ Ang Mo Kio Djitsun mall
content: seems like a good place to have indian food. briyani a must ry. Love Mr. Mari's service. great fod and the ambience is just wow
Bo Bo and Leong Tai Yoke were serving us. They are very patience and very polite to us. We have a very pleasant and enjoyable dinner. Will surely come back again.

restaurant name: Al Fatthah Food Expo Restaurant Indian Muslim Food Thai Muslim Seafood
content:
Good place to go to for some sinful supper :P

There‚Äôs abit of waiting time so good to call them beforehand to order. Prices can be quite steep here. Maggie pattaya was $7 but granted it had chicken and seafood.

Best Mexican food in Singapore!

To be sure, there aren't many options for Mexican food on the island. Nevertheless, Guzman y Gomez food is generally high quality and eminently edible ... Though it may not compare to taco truck food in LA!

I stick to the spicy beef option for most dishes with the burrito or burrito bowl being my preferred choice. The quesadillas are also decent.

If in Singapore and craving Mexican food then GYG is your only choice. Thankfully, they have multiple outlets across the city to satisfy your craving.

restaurant name: The Xiang Pavilion ÂõΩËâ≤Â§©Êπò Ôºà Guo Se Tian Xiang Ôºâ
content: Decent authentic Hunan food in a comfortable setting at an affordable price.  Could be spicier though!

Presentation can be better improved. The beef portion size (which requires top up) was even smaller than the chicken (which requires no top up).. the taste wise is okay but can do with much more meat as only vegetables can be seen in the tacos.
The briyani was Fantastic. The prata was crispy and fluffy. The curry was superb.

This is like the most awesome food court ever, full of delicious, freshly cooked Malaysian delicacies. Large and airy, finding a seat is usually not a problem after a short wait especially after the recent expansion. My favourites here include the Penang Char Kuay Teow, their steamed chicken (buy half chicken to share for better value, at $12), and the Gohtong Jaya Zi char stall. The rest of the other stalls are good too but these few are the standouts!

If you like mee rebus, you must try this stall. The gravy is thick and tasty. They added a scoop of satay sauce to the gravy before serving which makes the taste unique. I added some chilli sauce (meant for mee soto) and it gave it a spicy punch.
Go for the Shanghai ÁîüÁÖéÂåÖ which is bursting with juices. Other items such as the dry noodles are also worth trying.

one of most reasonable priced eatery in Yishun.  Managed by mainlander Chinese, the food is tasty (not salty), generous portions.  My favourites have been the cucumber side dish with garlic, vinegar and parley (great appetizer), the dumplings - steamed or fried are just as great and the noodles!!  There are too many to list out.  Try it out - before noons on weekdays and prepare to queue on weekends!!

Haven't been to Mouth Restaurant for many years... scored the 7 course Boston Lobster set meal for 5pax at $148nett. So a group of 7 of us went. The portion is big enough for 6 actually. All the dishes were very flavourful.
The highlight of the meal was the liu sha bao. 1 of the best I had ever eaten - the skin is polo bun style - very thin and a bit crispy, the filling overflowing when we bit into it... Chilli crab bun was nice too.
Surprisingly, all their vegetarian dishes were made very well too. And good value.
Very tasty and delicious fishball.very flavourful n fried cubed pork lard makes the dish go WOW!!
Store owners are very friendly and their baked pasta is really good! Will highly recommend to my friends and will definitely visit again :) Thank you!
Noodles is good and tasty, handmade fishcake is not too bad but the fish ball is a little fishy and mushy. But overall everything is good. Be sure to Q for a good 15 mins.

Spent our Sunday morning having #Dimsum
ü•ü
It has been a long time since we last came. Service is prompt and dimsum taste pretty ok. There is a lot of variety and service is prompt in serving. A bit pricey but overall it is decent.
Came here twice. Price is good and food is nice. Came once for lunch and once just for coffee. Found my favourite fresh milk with coffee ice cubes here. Will definitely return to eat again.
6.8SD for such a big bowel of rice noodle! Plus quite tasty ! Can‚Äôt believe it‚Äôs so cheap ( In singapore)

I've eaten at Putien many times, great meal each time. This is the first time ordering "to-go", and I'm reviewing during covid time when quality and service matters the most. The food were packed in an insulated bag. Container material and design was of quality, the sweet and sour sauce was separated from the meat (not shown in photo). Chopsticks were solid wood. I really appreciate the restaurant's position to maintain the quality in their food and brand. üëçüèº
Nice, authentic and Affordable price for Teochew cuisine with dim sum
Roast duck, egg tart & crispy bbq pork bun are recommended. However, the molten salted egg yolk piggy bun was a big disappointment. It‚Äôs more like a paste than ‚Äúmolten‚Äù. Cute but not worth it.

Tried the ramen before taking vaccination at Braddell Medical Clinic.
Indeed very flavourful and rich with the Tonkatsu aroma. However, in personal taste might find it a bit salty. Reasonably priced at 6.90 for a restaurant-like ramen.
Friendly and affordable pricing,  I like the prata that come with ikan bilis sambal chilli,  not as usual in Singapore prata eateries
Served precooked BBQ Chicken which was hard and cold.

My takeaway order had been missed and I needed to wait for a long time until staff noticed. Then, they forgot to provide utensils for burrito bowls.Not sure if it is due to staff shortage, but unless you dont remind them, they dont seem to bother tracking the things in order. Food is not bad but service is lacking.

restaurant name: Toa Payoh West Market & Food Centre (Lorong 1)
content:
Fairly empty at time of visit (10am Friday).
Stores with constant queue were the roast meat store, main tauhuey store, hokkien mee store.

Ordered the famous carrot cake large size $4, took about 40mins. Not as nice as I recall and frankly even too salty, and this was after I had my other dishes. Wouldn‚Äôt have it again.

Had the large size $3.50 mee Siam, it was really good and I would be happy to have it again. Auntie squeezes the lime juice for you so you don‚Äôt have to do it yourself.

The tauhuey $1 was good but I didn‚Äôt prefer it. Though silky somehow I felt there was no more soybean taste. It felt like I was eating agarAgar or pudding‚Ä¶

Hokkien mee smallest size $5, was really good. It was flavorful, umami, good taste of lard without the porky taste. Chilli was not my fav but the base noodles itself was way too good already. Would have it again but it is a big portion for the smallest size.

Toapayoh HC is not bad. Was wondering why it was quite empty today but realised must have been because of the current covid cluster here . Lol‚Ä¶

No frills yakiniku outlet at AMK hub. Our first visit here. Jun Ming was patient enough to explain how the restaurant works (different from Suntec) and introduce us their seasonal menu (Hokkaido pork) which is a must-try.

Even though queue was pretty long, it was moving along just fine. We had a great dinner and would be back again in the future. üôÇ

Only saving grace was the service provided by our server (despite the lack of staff), and the average food quality.

Other than that, horrible experience & will never go back again. Food took so long to be served for the set menu for 8 pax. Ordered a separate portion of fried rice without seafood due to severe seafood allergy at the second course & we did mention it to our server. But it took 1.5 hours to be served! What's worse?! It came with crab meat in the dish! Luckily the diner noticed it or she would have ended up in the hospital already!

Before that when I went to check if the fried rice was ready due to the ridiculously long wait, I saw 2-3 servers picking out seafood from a plate of fried rice (I thought it wasn't for my table hence didn't say anything). Hello, do you guys know what is severe seafood allergy & how serious it can be how?! How can you just freaking pick out from the plate of rice & serve it, misleading customers to think that it is cooked seafood free. But thankfully because you guys just picked out the crabmeat like that, the diner still managed to spot leftover huge chunks of crabmeat before she took more than one bite or all of us would have ended up opposite at TTSH worrying for her life already!

Poor diner only had dessert to eat for the entire 2.5 hours. Thanks for the "wonderful" experience that we would never have imagined to receive from such a well established & famous restaurant.

Only the San Lou Bee Hoon is nice (4.5 out of 5.). The garlic fried chicken is decent (3.8 out of 5). The Da Lou Mee is terrible (2.0 out of 5), but generous amount of pork lard was given. Will come back for the San Lou Bee Hoon and maybe try out their Claypot Rice next time.
The food was so good they even give us mala duck bone at the end for free, damn good siak

Dined here twice and was always impressed by the portion size and quality. Very value for money üëçüèª

Was blown away by how they went as far as using a wooden board to serve my grilled salmon! (Take note that this is in a neighbourhood coffee shop that is hidden from main road so they could have just save the effort and no one will mind)

Overheard the plump auntie counter staff chided the young chef for being crazy to be so elaborate, and he replied "Aiya, I just want customer to receive their food as close to how the pics look".

For this good attitude and food, I think they deserve a 5 star rating! ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
Good old brand that can be trusted for some authentic and good Chinese food. Been around since my grandparents time! Value for money
Nice

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Food is yummy ! Service is superb !!! Especially promotion for the kronenbourg Blanc $28.80 and Sapporo white ($58) . My family was very happy and enjoys .. must come!  ÔøΩ ‚Ä¶
Love this place! Home cooked
Best home cooked meals EVER! Sweet and sour pork & the ginger onion with fish were amazing.
Pizza is 5/10. Taste like those frozen one in the supermarket. If you are looking for a quiet place, look elsewhere. It is next to a bowl place so noise is inevitable.

*This review is specifically for this dish only.

Taste:
This is one of the best chilli ban mian I have eaten.
The noodles texture is chewy and bouncy, the mushroom and the egg yolk taste combined is just perfect.

Price:
Pretty decent, I can‚Äôt remember the price, but this is definitely below $5.

Service:
Dined at a pretty odd hour after the common dinner timings so there are still seats available. For this specific stall, the food was served pretty quickly.

This Jones is definitely better than the other Jones. Food wise/price wise all win. The presentation u know they put in effort. Sweet corn/coleslaw and yes the curly fries definitely on point. So for anyone who wants a decent western meal can come here and try out their huge variety of choices . I will be definitely be back to try all their food on the menu. Shangri-la chef ok don't play play .....
‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è extra stars for the amazing service! food is glorious and the cheese is SO TOASTY!!! & they use paper bags too??? we love a sustainable business!!!!!

restaurant name: Suki-Suki Thai Hot Pot @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content:
Not worth paying $25.90++ and another weekend dinner surcharge of $3++ per pax and another $10.90++ for premium items but the restaurant is short handed.

You have its staff doubling between Suki-Suki Thai and Siam Kitchen and honestly, you can get something comparable somewhere else at a more affordable price.
sauce is really nice. very good service. friendly staff

Good service but the prices has got up quite a bit. The hot soup based has not changed much through the years. Wished the had more local flavour like laksa etc..... We always go for the tomyam soup base. The personal pot style is expensive, to save money we always only order one small pot to share. Even with only one soup pot, the bill for two was over SGD80.
Service excellent. Dong, Ivan, Ivy,yy

My family & I liked this place food and overall Lao Hero kitchen food are good not too salty but tasty n environment is also nice . Now they have promotion for 2 crabs $60 & can cook 2 types of sauces & foc 6 buns. Worth to eatüòãüòãüòãüòã.

Nice ambience. Friendly and fast service. The"food shuttle" is gimmicky, but it does speed up the service.
Food is average. Matcha powder for your green tea is a welcome so you can adjust the concentration to your taste.
Prices are reasonable for the place and service.
Food is reasonably priced and yummy. Staff are welcoming. All should try.
Overall quality of food is good though the fried stuff can be a bit too oily. Friendly service staff. Relaxed environment and an overall satisfying dining experience.

Excellent service and affordable place to eat . Staff was very polite and explains to us regards the Halal certificate. Food was great , taste like the high class restaurant. Highly recommend place to dine in.  I will come back again to try out the rest of the menu.

restaurant name: Signature Restaurant & Bar - Best Briyani and Grill chicken
content:
Decent Indian food. Not too expensive. Convenient location. Was not too crowded as well.
Will repeat.
The 2.30-4.30pm discount is good. Ingredients are fresh and broth is also tasty. Love their mala broth.

restaurant name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
content: nice place, lots of menu choices
Very nice Thai food!! Cheap and affordable. Tried the basil pork and Tom yam fried rice. Both is dam good!
Feel like home food.
Not bad..will try more dish next visit

$1.50 per kosong prata. Elsewhere could be cheaper. But the clean environment and one of the nicest prata we have eaten so far deserve the high price.
The curry serving is enough for 2 pratas. We feel more is needed if order more than 2.

restaurant name: Tasty Loong at Orto Park ÈæçÈ≤úÈñ£
content: Like the place next to fish pond, food is tasty and good presentation
Amazing tasty Indian chinese food and Indian foods.wonderful delicious restaurant

restaurant name: ANDES by ASTONS @ SAFRA Toa Payoh
content: Restaurant was only half full on a Friday Lunch hour. Orders took 45 mins to arrive. Kitchen was extremely slow compared to other outlets. If you want to eat ASTONS suggest to patronise their other outlets.
One of the old skool type of western food ...been eating since young where they are formerly @ S11  blk 711 coffeeshop & now after @ blk347
A must try Penang fried kueh tiao!!!

First had sushi-go at the Jurong Point outlet, it was pretty good and worth the price. When the AMK Hub outlet opened, the queue was superrrrr long and they close the queue as early as 7pm (on a weekday!!) Food doesn‚Äôt seem to be as good anymore, kitchen seems to be messy as a few of our orders were messed up (gave the wrong item, sent the same item twice, food did not come after awhile). Probably not worth the wait at the amk outlet ü•≤

supper lovers.. this is the place where you can go..! it closes at 1am..
food is bad...! $12.90 for a whole steam fish.. Cheap! But it is on promo.. not sure when it will end..

why 4 stars? cos i got bitten by mozzy while dinning there..

Dishonest and low quality food. Don‚Äôt waste your time. We asked for red grouper. They gave us a black/pearl grouper instead and still charged us $76 for the fish. Total was $92 and fish was not even fresh.

First and last time eating here.

Have been here a few times but I feel the need to review my latest visit. We had to wait for almost an hour (see photo attached). There was Raydy-o silence from the restaurant's Instagram despite the numerous tags. And when the food arrived, the ingredients in the soup were barely cooked. One can only wonder how a dish that took close to an hour to prepare could somehow arrive undercooked. Did the bowl take a detour through Antarctica? My friends and I soldiered through because we did not want our stomachs to be held hostage for another 60mins. After the "meal", we let the cashier know about the state of the food. The cashier could only apologise. Having been wronged in time and in taste, I feel the customer service, like the dish, was undercooked.
My always favourite eating places with family

1/5

Service was POOR, oh wait absolutely no service at all. Yet, there was still 10% service charge. Food was served via a conveyor belt - so where‚Äôs the service in that? And they made me queue for 20 mins just to foot the bill? Absolutely pathetic. The cashier was just have a casual conversation with another customer which held up the entire queue. Talk about customer service - really??

As for the food, it completely lacked quality. For the price charged, you‚Äôd have a better time at other more establish dim sum places. Ordered the white bait fish which felt like it was just a plate of fried flour. The prawn dumpling was sticky and tasted bland af. The conveyor belt also served one of our dishes to ANOTHER table before sending it back. Come on la

The only saving grace‚Ä¶ oh wait none. This place is definitely not worth going - skip it babes.

As usual slow, and the server staff is impolite, including the chef. Ask for top up gravy for masala chicken, was informed no? First time I hear of this. Wanted pack thosai and was informed kitchen cannot cope?? Not making.. coffee, tea came quite cold, apparently left out in open before serve. Service need to improve and steamline items. Going downhill, as I don‚Äôt find it as good as before at springleaf branch. That outlet also have service issue. That is another story.

Best plate of Malay Style Nasi Lemak i had tried in years. It‚Äôs so good that i went back to Q for it for 2 straight days. The rice is amazing, cook till perfect. The chili is flavourful not too spicy. The chicken wings is not perfect. The fish is crispy on outside and not too dry inside. The whole combinations is well orchestrated.
Tried this after reading good reviews. Their chicken curry and beef rendang is good but overall price is a bit steep for coffeeshop setting. The meal for 3 costs me $33.50. üò≠
Indian restaurant where you can find indian foods but not that much tasty.

restaurant name: Muslim Delights Malay Food and Noodles
content: Great tasting nasi Padang. The portions are generally quite sizable and the dishes are absolutely tasty. The rendang was reasonably tender but I felt the Sayur lodeh was a little bit too watery for my taste. Still a good visit and I‚Äôll definitely be back. Parking nearby is horrible unless you ride a bike.

Where is mine pulut hitam? When i reach home i found mine pulut hitam is missing.How can i claim this?On top of that the rice roll not even give me the sauce. A bit disappointed. Can one staff help to do QC on the food packaging to make sure everything is in order plsss.
Wow.. never lost its tastes..  the dishes are all so authentic  like the gado gado n rebus is my favorites.. not forgetting the yummy satay, etc.
The assam laksa is not bad but quite spicy! üå∂ the char kway teow is above average, same as the chendol. Might go again if I‚Äôm missing these famous Penang food.
5 stars service, staff very patient and polite. They have special food and drink. Delicious and satisfying. The pet friendly zone is spacious without worrying about rain or hot weather.
Decent Indian food. Always crowded but nice communal vibe to the plave. No frills.
GREW UP EATING UNCLE'S WESTERN FOOD SINCE HE WAS AT CLEMENTI AVE 4. 26 YEARS DOWN THE ROAD , THO DIFFERENT LOCATION , STILL GO BACK TO HAVE THIS WHOLESOME WESTERN FOOD.

Wasn‚Äôt crowded during the dinner period.
Decent ramen with generous portion.
The Karaage was too salty.. but quite tasty if you brush the sauce aside. Tomato cheese ramen is surprisingly pleasant. However, the beef ramen wasn‚Äôt that good and it had the very strong beefy smell üòÖ

Had the mee rebus, mee siam and nasi lemak with ikan bilis, all in all an average meal which was made value for money as the price for the food is cheap. Rare find in Singapore with prices this cheap!

MY FAVOURITE INDIAN RESTAURANT.
Their soya, Tahu sambal & potato are the best!
Clean and service are tiptop.
Was nice to see the boss's children helping around in the restaurant too...
A well maintained reputation and quality of food and service that has only gotten better over the years...
The taste is unlike the usual Mee rebus you find elsewhere. The gravy is sweet and if you get the Mee Rebus extra special, they'll add a huge chicken drumstick with satay gravy.

Mixed fish soup (default comes with milk) was a hearty substantial bowl. Felt full even without adding rice or noodles. Soup and batang was as expected but fried fish was exceptionally good, light batter and huge chunks. Not sure what fish was used though, dory? Fish soup purists may automatically opt for the traditional batang soup but I'd say give the mixed one a try! Chilli with garlic also seemed homemade and was very good.
